var P_HTM = [];
P_HTM[1]="*Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa* **";
P_HTM[2]="*Vinayapiṭake* **";
P_HTM[3]="*Mahāvaggapāḷi* **";
P_HTM[4]="*1. Kammakkhandhaka **1.  The chapter on legal procedures *";
P_HTM[5]="*1. Tajjanīyakamma**1. The legal procedure of condemnation*";
P_HTM[6]="*Namo tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sammāsambuddhassa.**Homage to the Buddha, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One*";
P_HTM[7]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[8]="*Tena kho pana samayena paṇḍukalohitakā bhikkhū attanā bhaṇḍanakārakā kalahakārakā vivādakārakā bhassakārakā saṅghe adhikaraṇakārakā, yepi caññe bhikkhū bhaṇḍanakārakā kalahakārakā vivādakārakā bhassakārakā saṅghe adhikaraṇakārakā te upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadanti—**At that time the monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka were quarrelsome, argumentative, and creators of legal issues in the Sangha. They went to other monks who were also quarrelsome, argumentative, and creators of legal issues in the Sangha, and said to them,*";
P_HTM[9]="*“mā kho tumhe, āyasmanto, eso ajesi.**“Don’t let him beat you.*";
P_HTM[10]="*Balavābalavaṃ paṭimantetha.**Argue back forcefully.*";
P_HTM[11]="*Tumhe tena paṇḍitatarā ca byattatarā ca bahussutatarā ca alamattatarā ca.**You’re wiser, more competent, more learned, and more capable than he.*";
P_HTM[12]="*Mā cassa bhāyittha.**Don’t be afraid of him.*";
P_HTM[13]="*Mayampi tumhākaṃ pakkhā bhavissāmā”ti.**We’ll take your side.”*";
P_HTM[14]="*Tena anuppannāni ceva bhaṇḍanāni uppajjanti uppannāni ca bhaṇḍanāni bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya saṃvattanti.**Because of that, new quarrels started and existing quarrels became worse.*";
P_HTM[15]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[16]="*“kathañhi nāma paṇḍukalohitakā bhikkhū attanā bhaṇḍanakārakā kalahakārakā vivādakārakā bhassakārakā saṅghe adhikaraṇakārakā, yepi caññe bhikkhū bhaṇḍanakārakā kalahakārakā vivādakārakā bhassakārakā saṅghe adhikaraṇakārakā te upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vakkhanti—**“How can the monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka act like this?”*";
P_HTM[17]="*‘mā kho tumhe, āyasmanto, eso ajesi.* **";
P_HTM[18]="*Balavābalavaṃ paṭimantetha.* **";
P_HTM[19]="*Tumhe tena paṇḍitatarā ca byattatarā ca bahussutatarā ca alamattatarā ca.* **";
P_HTM[20]="*Mā cassa bhāyittha.* **";
P_HTM[21]="*Mayampi tumhākaṃ pakkhā bhavissāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[22]="*Tena anuppannāni ceva bhaṇḍanāni uppajjanti uppannāni ca bhaṇḍanāni bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya saṃvattantī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[23]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[24]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[25]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, paṇḍukalohitakā bhikkhū attanā bhaṇḍanakārakā kalahakārakā vivādakārakā bhassakārakā saṅghe adhikaraṇakārakā, yepi caññe bhikkhū bhaṇḍanakārakā kalahakārakā vivādakārakā bhassakārakā saṅghe adhikaraṇakārakā te upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadanti—**“Is it true that the monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka are acting like this?”*";
P_HTM[26]="*‘mā kho tumhe, āyasmanto, eso ajesi.* **";
P_HTM[27]="*Balavābalavaṃ paṭimantetha.* **";
P_HTM[28]="*Tumhe tena paṇḍitatarā ca byattatarā ca bahussutatarā ca alamattatarā ca.* **";
P_HTM[29]="*Mā cassa bhāyittha.* **";
P_HTM[30]="*Mayampi tumhākaṃ pakkhā bhavissāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[31]="*Tena anuppannāni ceva bhaṇḍanāni uppajjanti, uppannāni ca bhaṇḍanāni bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya saṃvattantī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[32]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[33]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—**The Buddha criticized them,*";
P_HTM[34]="*“ananucchavikaṃ, bhikkhave, tesaṃ moghapurisānaṃ ananulomikaṃ appatirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ akaraṇīyaṃ.**“It’s not suitable for those foolish men, it’s not proper, it’s not worthy of a monastic, it’s not allowable, it’s not to be done.*";
P_HTM[35]="*Kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā attanā bhaṇḍanakārakā …pe…**How can they act like this,*";
P_HTM[36]="*saṅghe adhikaraṇakārakā, yepi caññe bhikkhū bhaṇḍanakārakā …pe…* **";
P_HTM[37]="*saṅghe adhikaraṇakārakā te upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vakkhanti—* **";
P_HTM[38]="*‘mā kho tumhe, āyasmanto, eso ajesi.* **";
P_HTM[39]="*Balavābalavaṃ paṭimantetha.* **";
P_HTM[40]="*Tumhe tena paṇḍitatarā ca byattatarā ca bahussutatarā ca alamattatarā ca.* **";
P_HTM[41]="*Mā cassa bhāyittha.* **";
P_HTM[42]="*Mayampi tumhākaṃ pakkhā bhavissāmā’ti?* **";
P_HTM[43]="*Tena anuppannāni ceva bhaṇḍanāni uppajjanti, uppannāni ca bhaṇḍanāni bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya saṃvattanti.**causing that new quarrels to start and existing quarrels to become worse?*";
P_HTM[44]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya pasannānaṃ vā bhiyyobhāvāya.**This will affect people’s confidence,*";
P_HTM[45]="*Atha khvetaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānañceva appasādāya pasannānañca ekaccānaṃ aññathattāyā”ti.**and cause some to lose it.”*";
P_HTM[46]="*Atha kho bhagavā te bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā dubbharatāya dupposatāya mahicchatāya asantuṭṭhitāya saṅgaṇikāya kosajjassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsitvā anekapariyāyena subharatāya suposatāya appicchassa santuṭṭhassa sallekhassa dhutassa pāsādikassa apacayassa vīriyārambhassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsitvā bhikkhūnaṃ tadanucchavikaṃ tadanulomikaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**The Buddha then spoke in many ways in dispraise of being difficult to support and maintain, in dispraise of great desires, discontent, socializing, and laziness; but he spoke in many ways in praise of being easy to support and maintain, of fewness of wishes, contentment, self-elimination, ascetic practices, serenity, reduction in things, and being energetic. After giving a teaching on what is right and proper, he addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[47]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho paṇḍukalohitakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ tajjanīyakammaṃ karotu.**“Well then, monks, the Sangha should do a legal procedure of condemnation against the monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka.*";
P_HTM[48]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, kātabbaṃ.**And this is how it should be done.*";
P_HTM[49]="*Paṭhamaṃ paṇḍukalohitakā bhikkhū codetabbā, codetvā sāretabbā, sāretvā āpattiṃ āropetabbā, āpattiṃ āropetvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**First you should accuse the monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka. They should then be reminded of what they have done, before they are charged with an offense. A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[50]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[51]="*Ime paṇḍukalohitakā bhikkhū attanā bhaṇḍanakārakā kalahakārakā vivādakārakā bhassakārakā saṅghe adhikaraṇakārakā, yepi caññe bhikkhū bhaṇḍanakārakā kalahakārakā vivādakārakā bhassakārakā saṅghe adhikaraṇakārakā te upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadanti—**These monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka are quarrelsome, argumentative, and creators of legal issues in the Sangha. They go to other monks who are also quarrelsome, argumentative, and creators of legal issues in the Sangha, and they say to them,*";
P_HTM[52]="*“mā kho tumhe, āyasmanto, eso ajesi.**“Don’t let him beat you.*";
P_HTM[53]="*Balavābalavaṃ paṭimantetha.**Argue back forcefully.*";
P_HTM[54]="*Tumhe tena paṇḍitatarā ca byattatarā ca bahussutatarā ca alamattatarā ca.**You’re wiser, more competent, more learned, and more capable than he.*";
P_HTM[55]="*Mā cassa bhāyittha.**Don’t be afraid of him.*";
P_HTM[56]="*Mayampi tumhākaṃ pakkhā bhavissāmā”ti.**We’ll take your side.”*";
P_HTM[57]="*Tena anuppannāni ceva bhaṇḍanāni uppajjanti, uppannāni ca bhaṇḍanāni bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya saṃvattanti.**Because of this, new quarrels start and existing quarrels become worse.*";
P_HTM[58]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho paṇḍukalohitakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ tajjanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should do a legal procedure of condemnation against the monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka.*";
P_HTM[59]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[60]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[61]="*Ime paṇḍukalohitakā bhikkhū attanā bhaṇḍanakārakā …pe…**These monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka are quarrelsome, argumentative,*";
P_HTM[62]="*saṅghe adhikaraṇakārakā,**and creators of legal issues in the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[63]="*yepi caññe bhikkhū bhaṇḍanakārakā …pe… saṅghe adhikaraṇakārakā te upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadanti—**They go to other monks who are also quarrelsome, argumentative, and creators of legal issues in the Sangha, and they say to them,*";
P_HTM[64]="*“mā kho tumhe, āyasmanto, eso ajesi.**“Don’t let him beat you.*";
P_HTM[65]="*Balavābalavaṃ paṭimantetha.**Argue back forcefully.*";
P_HTM[66]="*Tumhe tena paṇḍitatarā ca byattatarā ca bahussutatarā ca alamattatarā ca.**You’re wiser, more competent, more learned, and more capable than he.*";
P_HTM[67]="*Mā cassa bhāyittha.**Don’t be afraid of him.*";
P_HTM[68]="*Mayampi tumhākaṃ pakkhā bhavissāmā”ti.**We’ll take your side.”*";
P_HTM[69]="*Tena anuppannāni ceva bhaṇḍanāni uppajjanti, uppannāni ca bhaṇḍanāni bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya saṃvattanti.**Because of this, new quarrels start and existing quarrels become worse.*";
P_HTM[70]="*Saṅgho paṇḍukalohitakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ tajjanīyakammaṃ karoti.**The Sangha does a legal procedure of condemnation against the monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka.*";
P_HTM[71]="*Yassāyasmato khamati paṇḍukalohitakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ tajjanīyassa kammassa karaṇaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of doing a legal procedure of condemnation against the monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[72]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[73]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—**For the second time I speak on this matter.*";
P_HTM[74]="*suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
