P_HTM[101]="*Kataṃ saṅghena paṇḍukalohitakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ tajjanīyakammaṃ.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of condemnation against the monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka.*";
P_HTM[102]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[103]="*1.1. Adhammakammadvādasaka**1.1 The group of twelve on illegitimate legal procedures*";
P_HTM[104]="*“Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgataṃ tajjanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.**“Monks, when a legal procedure of condemnation has three qualities, it is illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[105]="*Asammukhā kataṃ hoti, appaṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, appaṭiññāya kataṃ hoti—**it is done in the absence of the accused, it is done without questioning the accused, it is done without the admission of the accused.*";
P_HTM[106]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ tajjanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[107]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ tajjanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.**When a procedure of condemnation has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[108]="*Anāpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adesanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, desitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti—**it is done against one who hasn’t committed any offense, it is done against one who has committed an offense that isn’t clearable by confession, it is done against one who has confessed their offense.*";
P_HTM[109]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ tajjanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[110]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ tajjanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.**When a procedure of condemnation has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[111]="*Acodetvā kataṃ hoti, asāretvā kataṃ hoti, āpattiṃ anāropetvā kataṃ hoti—**it is done without having accused the person of their offense, it is done without having reminded the person of their offense, it is done without having charged the person with their offense.*";
P_HTM[112]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ tajjanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[113]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ tajjanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.**“When a procedure of condemnation has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[114]="*Asammukhā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti—**it is done in the absence of the accused, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
