P_HTM[178]="*Dhammakammadvādasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of twelve on legitimate legal procedures is finished.*";
P_HTM[179]="*1.3. Ākaṅkhamānachakka**1.3 The group of six on wishing*";
P_HTM[180]="*Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, tajjanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**“When a monk has three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a legal procedure of condemnation against him:*";
P_HTM[181]="*Bhaṇḍanakārako hoti kalahakārako vivādakārako bhassakārako saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako;**he is quarrelsome, argumentative, and a creator of legal issues in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[182]="*bālo hoti abyatto āpattibahulo anapadāno;**he is ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, incapable of determining whether he has committed an offense;*";
P_HTM[183]="*gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi—**he is constantly and improperly socializing with householders.*";
P_HTM[184]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, tajjanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[185]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, tajjanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**When a monk has another three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of condemnation against him:*";
P_HTM[186]="*Adhisīle sīlavipanno hoti, ajjhācāre ācāravipanno hoti, atidiṭṭhiyā diṭṭhivipanno hoti—**he has failed in the higher morality; he has failed in conduct; he has failed in view.*";
P_HTM[187]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, tajjanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[188]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, tajjanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**When a monk has another three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of condemnation against him:*";
P_HTM[189]="*Buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—**he disparages the Buddha; he disparages the Teaching; he disparages the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[190]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, tajjanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[191]="*Tiṇṇaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, tajjanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**“The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of condemnation against three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[192]="*Eko bhaṇḍanakārako hoti kalahakārako vivādakārako bhassakārako saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako;**those who are quarrelsome, argumentative, and creators of legal issues in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[193]="*eko bālo hoti abyatto āpattibahulo anapadāno;**those who are ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, incapable of determining whether they have committed an offense;*";
P_HTM[194]="*eko gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi—**those who are constantly and improperly socializing with householders.*";
P_HTM[195]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, tajjanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[196]="*Aparesampi, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, tajjanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of condemnation against another three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[197]="*Eko adhisīle sīlavipanno hoti, eko ajjhācāre ācāravipanno hoti, eko atidiṭṭhiyā diṭṭhivipanno hoti—**those who have failed in the higher morality; those who have failed in conduct; those who have failed in view.*";
P_HTM[198]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, tajjanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[199]="*Aparesampi, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, tajjanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of condemnation against another three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[200]="*Eko buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, eko dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, eko saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—**those who disparage the Buddha; those who disparage the Teaching; those who disparage the Sangha.”*";
P_HTM[201]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, tajjanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[202]="*Ākaṅkhamānachakkaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of six on wishing is finished.*";
P_HTM[203]="*1.4. Aṭṭhārasavatta**1.4 The eighteen kinds of conduct*";
P_HTM[204]="*Tajjanīyakammakatena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā sammā vattitabbaṃ.**“A monk who has had a legal procedure of condemnation done against himself should conduct himself properly.*";
P_HTM[205]="*Tatrāyaṃ sammāvattanā—**This is the proper conduct:*";
P_HTM[206]="*na upasampādetabbaṃ,**He should not give the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[207]="*na nissayo dātabbo,**He should not give formal support.*";
P_HTM[208]="*na sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo,**He should not have a novice monk attend on him.*";
P_HTM[209]="*na bhikkhunovādakasammuti sāditabbā,**He should not accept being appointed as an instructor of the nuns.*";
P_HTM[210]="*sammatenapi bhikkhuniyo na ovaditabbā.**Even if appointed, he should not instruct the nuns.*";
P_HTM[211]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena tajjanīyakammaṃ kataṃ hoti sā āpatti na āpajjitabbā,**He should not commit the same offense as the offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of condemnation against him.*";
P_HTM[212]="*aññā vā tādisikā,**He should not commit an offense similar to the offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of condemnation against him.*";
P_HTM[213]="*tato vā pāpiṭṭhatarā;**He should not commit an offense worse than the offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of condemnation against him.*";
P_HTM[214]="*kammaṃ na garahitabbaṃ,**He should not criticize the procedure.*";
P_HTM[215]="*kammikā na garahitabbā.**He should not criticize those who did the procedure.*";
P_HTM[216]="*Na pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposatho ṭhapetabbo,**He should not cancel the observance-day procedure of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[217]="*na pavāraṇā ṭhapetabbā,**He should not cancel the invitation procedure of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[218]="*na savacanīyaṃ kātabbaṃ,**He should not speak to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him.*";
P_HTM[219]="*na anuvādo paṭṭhapetabbo,**He should not make accusations against a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[220]="*na okāso kāretabbo,**He should not ask a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense.*";
P_HTM[221]="*na codetabbo,**He should not accuse a regular monk of an offense.*";
P_HTM[222]="*na sāretabbo,**He should not remind a regular monk of an offense.*";
P_HTM[223]="*na bhikkhūhi sampayojetabban”ti.**He should not associate inappropriately with other monks.”*";
P_HTM[224]="*Tajjanīyakamme aṭṭhārasavattaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The eighteen kinds of conduct in regard to the legal procedure of condemnation are finished.*";
P_HTM[225]="*1.5. Nappaṭippassambhetabbaaṭṭhārasaka**1.5 The group of eighteen on not to be lifted*";
P_HTM[226]="*Atha kho saṅgho paṇḍukalohitakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ tajjanīyakammaṃ akāsi.**When the Sangha had done a legal procedure of condemnation against the monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka,*";
P_HTM[227]="*Te saṅghena tajjanīyakammakatā sammā vattanti, lomaṃ pātenti, netthāraṃ vattanti, bhikkhū upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadanti—**they conducted themselves properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released. They then went to the monks*";
P_HTM[228]="*“mayaṃ, āvuso, saṅghena tajjanīyakammakatā sammā vattāma, lomaṃ pātema, netthāraṃ vattāma, kathaṃ nu kho amhehi paṭipajjitabban”ti?**and told them about this, adding, “What should we do now?”*";
P_HTM[229]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …**The monks told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[230]="*pe….**He had the monks gathered and said,*";
P_HTM[231]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho paṇḍukalohitakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ tajjanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetu.**“Well then, lift that legal procedure of condemnation against the monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka.*";
P_HTM[232]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno tajjanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has five qualities, a legal procedure of condemnation against him should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[233]="*Upasampādeti, nissayaṃ deti, sāmaṇeraṃ upaṭṭhāpeti, bhikkhunovādakasammutiṃ sādiyati, sammatopi bhikkhuniyo ovadati—**he gives the full ordination; he gives formal support; he has a novice monk attend on him; he accepts being appointed as an instructor of the nuns; he instructs the nuns, whether appointed or not.*";
P_HTM[234]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno tajjanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[235]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno tajjanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of condemnation against him should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[236]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena tajjanīyakammaṃ kataṃ hoti taṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati, aññaṃ vā tādisikaṃ, tato vā pāpiṭṭhataraṃ;**he commits the same offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of condemnation against him; he commits an offense similar to the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of condemnation against him; he commits an offense worse than the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of condemnation against him;*";
P_HTM[237]="*kammaṃ garahati, kammike garahati—**he criticizes the procedure; he criticizes those who did the procedure.*";
P_HTM[238]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno tajjanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[239]="*Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno tajjanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has eight qualities, a procedure of condemnation against him should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[240]="*Pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposathaṃ ṭhapeti, pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapeti, savacanīyaṃ karoti, anuvādaṃ paṭṭhapeti, okāsaṃ kāreti, codeti, sāreti, bhikkhūhi sampayojeti—**he cancels the observance-day procedure of a regular monk; he cancels the invitation procedure of a regular monk; he speaks to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him; he makes accusations against a regular monk; he asks a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense; he accuses a regular monk of an offense; he reminds a regular monk of an offense; he associates inappropriately with other monks.”*";
P_HTM[241]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno tajjanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[242]="*Nappaṭippassambhetabbaaṭṭhārasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of eighteen on not to be lifted is finished.*";
P_HTM[243]="*1.6. Paṭippassambhetabbaaṭṭhārasaka**1.6 The group of eighteen on to be lifted*";
P_HTM[244]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno tajjanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**“When a monk has five qualities, a legal procedure of condemnation against him should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[245]="*Na upasampādeti, na nissayaṃ deti, na sāmaṇeraṃ upaṭṭhāpeti, na bhikkhunovādakasammutiṃ sādiyati, sammatopi bhikkhuniyo na ovadati—**he does not give the full ordination; he does not give formal support; he does not have a novice monk attend on him; he does not accept being appointed as an instructor of the nuns; he does not instruct the nuns, whether appointed or not.*";
P_HTM[246]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno tajjanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[247]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno tajjanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of condemnation against him should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[248]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena tajjanīyakammaṃ kataṃ hoti taṃ āpattiṃ na āpajjati, aññaṃ vā tādisikaṃ, tato vā pāpiṭṭhataraṃ;**he doesn’t commit the same offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of condemnation against him; he doesn’t commit an offense similar to the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of condemnation against him; he doesn’t commit an offense worse than the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of condemnation against him;*";
P_HTM[249]="*kammaṃ na garahati, kammike na garahati—**he doesn’t criticize the procedure; he doesn’t criticize those who did the procedure.*";
P_HTM[250]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno tajjanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[251]="*Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno tajjanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has eight qualities, a procedure of condemnation against him should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[252]="*Na pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposathaṃ ṭhapeti, na pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapeti, na savacanīyaṃ karoti, na anuvādaṃ paṭṭhapeti, na okāsaṃ kāreti, na codeti, na sāreti, na bhikkhūhi sampayojeti—**he doesn’t cancel the observance-day procedure of a regular monk; he doesn’t cancel the invitation procedure of a regular monk; he doesn’t speak to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him; he doesn’t make accusations against a regular monk; he doesn’t ask a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense; he doesn’t accuse a regular monk of an offense; he doesn’t remind a regular monk of an offense; he doesn’t associate inappropriately with other monks.”*";
P_HTM[253]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, tajjanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[254]="*Paṭippassambhetabbaaṭṭhārasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of eighteen on to be lifted is finished.*";
P_HTM[255]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**“And this is how it should be lifted.*";
P_HTM[256]="*Tehi, bhikkhave, paṇḍukalohitakehi bhikkhūhi saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**After approaching the Sangha, the monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka should put their upper robes over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on their heels, raise their joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[257]="*‘mayaṃ, bhante, saṅghena tajjanīyakammakatā sammā vattāma, lomaṃ pātema, netthāraṃ vattāma, tajjanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācāmā’ti.**‘Venerables, the Sangha has done a legal procedure of condemnation against us, but we have conducted ourselves properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released. We ask for the legal procedure of condemnation to be lifted.’*";
P_HTM[258]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbā.**And they should ask a second*";
P_HTM[259]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[260]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[261]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[262]="*Ime paṇḍukalohitakā bhikkhū saṅghena tajjanīyakammakatā sammā vattanti, lomaṃ pātenti, netthāraṃ vattanti, tajjanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācanti.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of condemnation against these monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka. They have conducted themselves properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now ask for the legal procedure of condemnation to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[263]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho paṇḍukalohitakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ tajjanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambheyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should lift the legal procedure of condemnation against the monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka.*";
P_HTM[264]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[265]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[266]="*Ime paṇḍukalohitakā bhikkhū saṅghena tajjanīyakammakatā sammā vattanti, lomaṃ pātenti, netthāraṃ vattanti, tajjanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācanti.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of condemnation against these monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka. They have conducted themselves properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now ask for the legal procedure of condemnation to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[267]="*Saṅgho paṇḍukalohitakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ tajjanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambheti.**The Sangha lifts the legal procedure of condemnation against the monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka.*";
P_HTM[268]="*Yassāyasmato khamati paṇḍukalohitakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ tajjanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhi, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of lifting the legal procedure of condemnation against the monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[269]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[270]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—**For the second time I speak on this matter.*";
P_HTM[271]="*suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[272]="*Ime paṇḍukalohitakā bhikkhū saṅghena tajjanīyakammakatā sammā vattanti, lomaṃ pātenti, netthāraṃ vattanti, tajjanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācanti.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of condemnation against these monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka. They have conducted themselves properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now ask for the legal procedure of condemnation to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[273]="*Saṅgho paṇḍukalohitakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ tajjanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambheti.**The Sangha lifts the legal procedure of condemnation against the monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka.*";
P_HTM[274]="*Yassāyasmato khamati paṇḍukalohitakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ tajjanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhi, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of lifting the legal procedure of condemnation against the monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[275]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[276]="*Tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—**For the third time I speak on this matter.*";
P_HTM[277]="*suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[278]="*Ime paṇḍukalohitakā bhikkhū saṅghena tajjanīyakammakatā sammā vattanti, lomaṃ pātenti, netthāraṃ vattanti, tajjanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācanti.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of condemnation against these monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka. They have conducted themselves properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now ask for the legal procedure of condemnation to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[279]="*Saṅgho paṇḍukalohitakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ tajjanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambheti.**The Sangha lifts the legal procedure of condemnation against the monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka.*";
P_HTM[280]="*Yassāyasmato khamati paṇḍukalohitakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ tajjanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhi, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of lifting the legal procedure of condemnation against the monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[281]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[282]="*Paṭippassaddhaṃ saṅghena paṇḍukalohitakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ tajjanīyakammaṃ.**The Sangha has lifted the legal procedure of condemnation against the monks Paṇḍuka and Lohitaka.*";
P_HTM[283]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[284]="*Tajjanīyakammaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ.**The first section on the legal procedure of condemnation is finished.*";
P_HTM[285]="*2. Niyassakamma**2. The legal procedure of demotion*";
P_HTM[286]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā seyyasako bālo hoti abyatto āpattibahulo anapadāno;**At that time Venerable Seyyasaka was ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, and incapable of determining whether he had committed an offense.*";
P_HTM[287]="*gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi;**And he was constantly and improperly socializing with householders.*";
P_HTM[288]="*apissu bhikkhū pakatā parivāsaṃ dentā mūlāya paṭikassantā mānattaṃ dentā abbhentā.**Moreover, the monks regularly gave him probation, sent him back to the beginning, gave him trial periods, and rehabilitated him.*";
P_HTM[289]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[290]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā seyyasako bālo bhavissati abyatto āpattibahulo anapadāno;**“How can Venerable Seyyasaka go on like this?”*";
P_HTM[291]="*gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharissati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi;* **";
P_HTM[292]="*apissu bhikkhū pakatā parivāsaṃ dentā mūlāya paṭikassantā mānattaṃ dentā abbhentā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[293]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**And they told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[294]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[295]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, seyyasako bhikkhu bālo abyatto āpattibahulo anapadāno;**“Is it true that the monk Seyyasaka goes on like this?”*";
P_HTM[296]="*gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi;* **";
P_HTM[297]="*apissu bhikkhū pakatā parivāsaṃ dentā mūlāya paṭikassantā mānattaṃ dentā abbhentā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[298]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[299]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—**The Buddha criticized him,*";
P_HTM[300]="*“ananucchavikaṃ, bhikkhave, tassa moghapurisassa ananulomikaṃ appatirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ akaraṇīyaṃ.**“It’s not suitable for that foolish man, it’s not proper, it’s not worthy of a monastic, it’s not allowable, it’s not to be done.*";
P_HTM[301]="*Kathañhi nāma so, bhikkhave, moghapuriso bālo bhavissati abyatto āpattibahulo anapadāno;**How can he be ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, and incapable of determining whether he has committed an offense?*";
P_HTM[302]="*gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharissati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi;**How can he constantly and improperly socialize with householders?*";
P_HTM[303]="*apissu bhikkhū pakatā parivāsaṃ dentā mūlāya paṭikassantā mānattaṃ dentā abbhentā.**Moreover, how can it be that the monks regularly give him probation, send him back to the beginning, give him trial periods, and rehabilitate him?*";
P_HTM[304]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[305]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing him …*";
P_HTM[306]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[307]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho seyyasakassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ karotu—**“Well then, the Sangha should do a legal procedure of demotion against the monk Seyyasaka,*";
P_HTM[308]="*nissāya te vatthabbanti.**instructing him to live with formal support.*";
P_HTM[309]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, kātabbaṃ.**And this is how it should be done.*";
P_HTM[310]="*Paṭhamaṃ seyyasako bhikkhu codetabbo, codetvā sāretabbo, sāretvā āpattiṃ āropetabbo, āpattiṃ āropetvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**First you should accuse the monk Seyyasaka. He should then be reminded of what he has done, before he is charged with an offense. A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[311]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[312]="*Ayaṃ seyyasako bhikkhu bālo abyatto āpattibahulo anapadāno;**The monk Seyyasaka is ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, and incapable of determining whether he has committed an offense.*";
P_HTM[313]="*gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi;**He is constantly and improperly socializing with householders.*";
P_HTM[314]="*apissu bhikkhū pakatā parivāsaṃ dentā mūlāya paṭikassantā mānattaṃ dentā abbhentā.**Moreover, the monks regularly give him probation, send him back to the beginning, give him the trial period, and rehabilitate him.*";
P_HTM[315]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho seyyasakassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ kareyya—**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should do a legal procedure of demotion against the monk Seyyasaka,*";
P_HTM[316]="*nissāya te vatthabbanti.**instructing him to live with formal support.*";
P_HTM[317]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[318]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[319]="*Ayaṃ seyyasako bhikkhu bālo abyatto āpattibahulo anapadāno;**The monk Seyyasaka is ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, and incapable of determining whether he has committed an offense.*";
P_HTM[320]="*gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi;**He is constantly and improperly socializing with householders.*";
P_HTM[321]="*apissu bhikkhū pakatā parivāsaṃ dentā mūlāya paṭikassantā mānattaṃ dentā abbhentā.**Moreover, the monks regularly give him probation, send him back to the beginning, give him the trial period, and rehabilitate him.*";
P_HTM[322]="*Saṅgho seyyasakassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ karoti—**The Sangha does a legal procedure of demotion against the monk Seyyasaka,*";
P_HTM[323]="*nissāya te vatthabbanti.**instructing him to live with formal support.*";
P_HTM[324]="*Yassāyasmato khamati seyyasakassa bhikkhuno niyassassa kammassa karaṇaṃ—**Any monk who approves of doing a legal procedure of demotion against the monk Seyyasaka,*";
P_HTM[325]="*nissāya te vatthabbanti, so tuṇhassa;**instructing him to live with formal support, should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[326]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[327]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[328]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—**For the third time I speak on this matter.*";
P_HTM[329]="*suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[330]="*Ayaṃ seyyasako bhikkhu bālo abyatto āpattibahulo anapadāno;**The monk Seyyasaka is ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, and incapable of determining whether he has committed an offense.*";
P_HTM[331]="*gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi;**He is constantly and improperly socializing with householders.*";
P_HTM[332]="*apissu bhikkhū pakatā parivāsaṃ dentā mūlāya paṭikassantā mānattaṃ dentā abbhentā.**Moreover, the monks regularly give him probation, send him back to the beginning, give him the trial period, and rehabilitate him.*";
P_HTM[333]="*Saṅgho seyyasakassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ karoti—**The Sangha does a legal procedure of demotion against the monk Seyyasaka,*";
P_HTM[334]="*nissāya te vatthabbanti.**instructing him to live with formal support.*";
P_HTM[335]="*Yassāyasmato khamati seyyasakassa bhikkhuno niyassassa kammassa karaṇaṃ—**Any monk who approves of doing a legal procedure of demotion against the monk Seyyasaka,*";
P_HTM[336]="*nissāya te vatthabbanti, so tuṇhassa;**instructing him to live with formal support, should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[337]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[338]="*Kataṃ saṅghena seyyasakassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ—**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of demotion against the monk Seyyasaka,*";
P_HTM[339]="*nissāya te vatthabbanti.**instructing him to live with formal support.*";
P_HTM[340]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[341]="*2.1. Adhammakammadvādasaka**2.1 The group of twelve on illegitimate legal procedures*";
P_HTM[342]="*“Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgataṃ niyassakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.**“When a legal procedure of demotion has three qualities, it is illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[343]="*Asammukhā kataṃ hoti, appaṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, appaṭiññāya kataṃ hoti—**it is done in the absence of the accused, it is done without questioning the accused, it is done without the admission of the accused.*";
P_HTM[344]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ niyassakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[345]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ niyassakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.**When a procedure of demotion has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[346]="*Anāpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adesanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, desitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti—**it is done against one who hasn’t committed any offense, it is done against one who has committed an offense that isn’t clearable by confession, it is done against one who has confessed their offense.*";
P_HTM[347]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ niyassakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[348]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ niyassakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.**When a procedure of demotion has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[349]="*Acodetvā kataṃ hoti, asāretvā kataṃ hoti, āpattiṃ anāropetvā kataṃ hoti—**it is done without having accused the person of their offense, it is done without having reminded the person of their offense, it is done without having charged the person with their offense.*";
P_HTM[350]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ niyassakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[351]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave …pe…**“When a procedure of demotion has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[352]="*asammukhā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti—**it is done in the absence of the accused, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[353]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave …pe….* **";
P_HTM[354]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave …pe…**When a procedure of demotion has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[355]="*appaṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti—**it is done without questioning the accused, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[356]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave …pe….* **";
P_HTM[357]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave …pe…**When a procedure of demotion has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[358]="*appaṭiññāya kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti—**it is done without the admission of the accused, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[359]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave …pe….* **";
P_HTM[360]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave …pe…**“When a procedure of demotion has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[361]="*anāpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti—**it is done against one who hasn’t committed any offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[362]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave …pe….* **";
P_HTM[363]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave …pe…**When a procedure of demotion has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[364]="*adesanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti—**it is done against one who has committed an offense that isn’t clearable by confession, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[365]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave …pe….* **";
P_HTM[366]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave …pe…**When a procedure of demotion has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[367]="*desitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti—**it is done against one who has confessed their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[368]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave …pe….* **";
P_HTM[369]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave …pe…**“When a procedure of demotion has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[370]="*acodetvā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti—**it is done without having accused the person of their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[371]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave …pe….* **";
P_HTM[372]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave …pe…**When a procedure of demotion has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[373]="*asāretvā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti—**it is done without having reminded the person of their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[374]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave …pe….* **";
P_HTM[375]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ niyassakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.**When a procedure of demotion has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[376]="*Āpattiṃ anāropetvā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti—**it is done without having charged the person with their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.”*";
P_HTM[377]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ niyassakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[378]="*Adhammakammadvādasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of twelve on illegitimate legal procedures is finished.*";
P_HTM[379]="*2.2. Dhammakammadvādasaka**2.2 The group of twelve on legitimate legal procedures*";
P_HTM[380]="*Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgataṃ niyassakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.**“When a legal procedure of demotion has three qualities, it is legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[381]="*Sammukhā kataṃ hoti, paṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, paṭiññāya kataṃ hoti—**it is done in the presence of the accused, it is done with the questioning of the accused, it is done with the admission of the accused.*";
P_HTM[382]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ niyassakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[383]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ niyassakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.**When a procedure of demotion has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[384]="*Āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, desanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adesitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti—**it is done against one who has committed an offense, it is done against one who has committed an offense that is clearable by confession, it is done against one who hasn’t confessed their offense.*";
P_HTM[385]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ niyassakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[386]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ niyassakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.**When a procedure of demotion has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[387]="*Codetvā kataṃ hoti, sāretvā kataṃ hoti, āpattiṃ āropetvā kataṃ hoti—**it is done after having accused the person of their offense, it is done after having reminded the person of their offense, it is done after having charged the person with their offense.*";
P_HTM[388]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ niyassakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[389]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave …pe…**“When a procedure of demotion has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[390]="*sammukhā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti—**it is done in the presence of the accused, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[391]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave …pe….* **";
P_HTM[392]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave …pe…**When a procedure of demotion has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[393]="*paṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti—**it is done with the questioning of the accused, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[394]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave …pe….* **";
P_HTM[395]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave …pe…**When a procedure of demotion has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[396]="*paṭiññāya kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti—**it is done with the admission of the accused, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[397]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave …pe….* **";
P_HTM[398]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave …pe…**“When a procedure of demotion has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[399]="*āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti—**it is done against one who has committed an offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[400]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave …pe….* **";
P_HTM[401]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave …pe…**When a procedure of demotion has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[402]="*desanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti—**it is done against one who has committed an offense that is clearable by confession, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[403]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave …pe….* **";
P_HTM[404]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave …pe…**When a procedure of demotion has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[405]="*adesitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti—**it is done against one who hasn’t confessed their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[406]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave …pe….* **";
P_HTM[407]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave …pe…**“When a procedure of demotion has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[408]="*codetvā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti—**it is done after having accused the person of their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[409]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave …pe….* **";
P_HTM[410]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave …pe…**When a procedure of demotion has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[411]="*sāretvā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti—**it is done after having reminded the person of their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[412]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave …pe….* **";
P_HTM[413]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ niyassakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.**When a procedure of demotion has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[414]="*Āpattiṃ āropetvā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti—**it is done after having charged the person with their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.”*";
P_HTM[415]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ niyassakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[416]="*Dhammakammadvādasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of twelve on legitimate legal procedures is finished.*";
P_HTM[417]="*2.3. Ākaṅkhamānachakka**2.3 The group of six on wishing*";
P_HTM[418]="*Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, niyassakammaṃ kareyya.**“When a monk has three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a legal procedure of demotion against him:*";
P_HTM[419]="*Bhaṇḍanakārako hoti kalahakārako vivādakārako bhassakārako saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako;**he is quarrelsome, argumentative, and a creator of legal issues in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[420]="*bālo hoti abyatto āpattibahulo anapadāno;**he is ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, incapable of determining whether he has committed an offense;*";
P_HTM[421]="*gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi—**he is constantly and improperly socializing with householders.*";
P_HTM[422]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, niyassakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[423]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, niyassakammaṃ kareyya.**When a monk has another three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of demotion against him:*";
P_HTM[424]="*Adhisīle sīlavipanno hoti, ajjhācāre ācāravipanno hoti, atidiṭṭhiyā diṭṭhivipanno hoti—**he has failed in the higher morality; he has failed in conduct; he has failed in view.*";
P_HTM[425]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, niyassakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[426]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, niyassakammaṃ kareyya.**When a monk has another three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of demotion against him:*";
P_HTM[427]="*Buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—**he disparages the Buddha; he disparages the Teaching; he disparages the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[428]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, niyassakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[429]="*Tiṇṇaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, niyassakammaṃ kareyya.**“The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of demotion against three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[430]="*Eko bhaṇḍanakārako hoti kalahakārako vivādakārako bhassakārako saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako;**those who are quarrelsome, argumentative, and creators of legal issues in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[431]="*eko bālo hoti, abyatto āpattibahulo anapadāno;**those who are ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, incapable of determining whether they have committed an offense;*";
P_HTM[432]="*eko gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi—**those who are constantly and improperly socializing with householders.*";
P_HTM[433]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, niyassakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[434]="*Aparesampi, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, niyassakammaṃ kareyya.**The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of demotion against another three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[435]="*Eko adhisīle sīlavipanno hoti, eko ajjhācāre ācāravipanno hoti, eko atidiṭṭhiyā diṭṭhivipanno hoti—**those who have failed in the higher morality; those who have failed in conduct; those who have failed in view.*";
P_HTM[436]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, niyassakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[437]="*Aparesampi, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, niyassakammaṃ kareyya.**The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of demotion against another three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[438]="*Eko buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, eko dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, eko saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—**those who disparage the Buddha; those who disparage the Teaching; those who disparage the Sangha.”*";
P_HTM[439]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, niyassakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[440]="*Ākaṅkhamānachakkaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of six on wishing is finished.*";
P_HTM[441]="*2.4. Aṭṭhārasavatta**2.4 The eighteen kinds of conduct*";
P_HTM[442]="*Niyassakammakatena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā sammā vattitabbaṃ.**“A monk who has had a legal procedure of demotion done against himself should conduct himself properly.*";
P_HTM[443]="*Tatrāyaṃ sammāvattanā—**This is the proper conduct:*";
P_HTM[444]="*na upasampādetabbaṃ,**He should not give the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[445]="*na nissayo dātabbo,**He should not give formal support.*";
P_HTM[446]="*na sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo,**He should not have a novice monk attend on him.*";
P_HTM[447]="*na bhikkhunovādakasammuti sāditabbā,**He should not accept being appointed as an instructor of the nuns.*";
P_HTM[448]="*sammatenapi bhikkhuniyo na ovaditabbā.**Even if appointed, he should not instruct the nuns.*";
P_HTM[449]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena niyassakammaṃ kataṃ hoti sā āpatti na āpajjitabbā,**He should not commit the same offense as the offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of demotion against him.*";
P_HTM[450]="*aññā vā tādisikā,**He should not commit an offense similar to the offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of demotion against him.*";
P_HTM[451]="*tato vā pāpiṭṭhatarā;**He should not commit an offense worse than the offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of demotion against him.*";
P_HTM[452]="*kammaṃ na garahitabbaṃ,**He should not criticize the procedure.*";
P_HTM[453]="*kammikā na garahitabbā.**He should not criticize those who did the procedure.*";
P_HTM[454]="*Na pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposatho ṭhapetabbo,**He should not cancel the observance-day procedure of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[455]="*na pavāraṇā ṭhapetabbā,**He should not cancel the invitation procedure of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[456]="*na savacanīyaṃ kātabbaṃ,**He should not speak to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him.*";
P_HTM[457]="*na anuvādo paṭṭhapetabbo,**He should not make accusations against a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[458]="*na okāso kārāpetabbo,**He should not ask a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense.*";
P_HTM[459]="*na codetabbo,**He should not accuse a regular monk of an offense.*";
P_HTM[460]="*na sāretabbo,**He should not remind a regular monk of an offense.*";
P_HTM[461]="*na bhikkhūhi sampayojetabban”ti.**He should not associate inappropriately with other monks.”*";
P_HTM[462]="*Niyassakamme aṭṭhārasavattaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The eighteen kinds of conduct in regard to the legal procedure of demotion are finished.*";
P_HTM[463]="*Atha kho saṅgho seyyasakassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ akāsi—**Soon the Sangha did a legal procedure of demotion against the monk Seyyasaka,*";
P_HTM[464]="*nissāya te vatthabbanti.**instructing him to live with formal support.*";
P_HTM[465]="*So saṅghena niyassakammakato kalyāṇamitte sevamāno bhajamāno payirupāsamāno uddisāpento paripucchanto bahussuto hoti, āgatāgamo dhammadharo vinayadharo mātikādharo paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī lajjī kukkuccako sikkhākāmo.**Then, by associating with good friends, by having them recite, and by questioning them, he became learned and a master of the tradition; he became an expert on the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the summaries; he became knowledgeable and competent, had a sense of conscience, and was afraid of wrongdoing and fond of the training.*";
P_HTM[466]="*Sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, bhikkhū upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeti—**And he conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released. He then went to the monks*";
P_HTM[467]="*“ahaṃ, āvuso, saṅghena niyassakammakato sammā vattāmi, lomaṃ pātemi, netthāraṃ vattāmi.**and told them about this,*";
P_HTM[468]="*Kathaṃ nu kho mayā paṭipajjitabban”ti?**adding, “What should I do now?”*";
P_HTM[469]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …**The monks told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[470]="*pe….**He had the monks gathered and said,*";
P_HTM[471]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho seyyasakassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ paṭippassambhetu.**“Well then, lift that legal procedure of demotion against the monk Seyyasaka.*";
P_HTM[472]="*2.5. Nappaṭippassambhetabbaaṭṭhārasaka**2.5 The group of eighteen on not to be lifted*";
P_HTM[473]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**“When a monk has five qualities, a legal procedure of demotion against him should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[474]="*Upasampādeti, nissayaṃ deti, sāmaṇeraṃ upaṭṭhāpeti, bhikkhunovādakasammutiṃ sādiyati, sammatopi bhikkhuniyo ovadati—**he gives the full ordination; he gives formal support; he has a novice monk attend on him; he accepts being appointed as an instructor of the nuns; he instructs the nuns, whether appointed or not.*";
P_HTM[475]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[476]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of demotion against him should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[477]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena niyassakammaṃ kataṃ hoti taṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati, aññaṃ vā tādisikaṃ, tato vā pāpiṭṭhataraṃ;**he commits the same offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of demotion against him; he commits an offense similar to the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of demotion against him; he commits an offense worse than the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of demotion against him;*";
P_HTM[478]="*kammaṃ garahati, kammike garahati—**he criticizes the procedure; he criticizes those who did the procedure.*";
P_HTM[479]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[480]="*Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has eight qualities, a legal procedure of demotion against him should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[481]="*Pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposathaṃ ṭhapeti, pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapeti, savacanīyaṃ karoti, anuvādaṃ paṭṭhapeti, okāsaṃ kāreti, codeti, sāreti, bhikkhūhi sampayojeti—**he cancels the observance-day procedure of a regular monk; he cancels the invitation procedure of a regular monk; he speaks to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him; he makes accusations against a regular monk; he asks a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense; he accuses a regular monk of an offense; he reminds a regular monk of an offense; he associates inappropriately with other monks.”*";
P_HTM[482]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[483]="*Nappaṭippassambhetabbaaṭṭhārasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of eighteen on not to be lifted is finished.*";
P_HTM[484]="*2.6. Paṭippassambhetabbaaṭṭhārasaka**2.6 The group of eighteen on to be lifted*";
P_HTM[485]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**“When a monk has five qualities, a legal procedure of demotion against him should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[486]="*Na upasampādeti, na nissayaṃ deti, na sāmaṇeraṃ upaṭṭhāpeti, na bhikkhunovādakasammutiṃ sādiyati, sammatopi bhikkhuniyo na ovadati—**he does not give the full ordination; he does not give formal support; he does not have a novice monk attend on him; he does not accept being appointed as an instructor of the nuns; he does not instruct the nuns, whether appointed or not.*";
P_HTM[487]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[488]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of demotion against him should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[489]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena niyassakammaṃ kataṃ hoti taṃ āpattiṃ na āpajjati, aññaṃ vā tādisikaṃ, tato vā pāpiṭṭhataraṃ;**he doesn’t commit the same offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of demotion against him; he doesn’t commit an offense similar to the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of demotion against him; he doesn’t commit an offense worse than the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of demotion against him;*";
P_HTM[490]="*kammaṃ na garahati, kammike na garahati—**he doesn’t criticize the procedure; he doesn’t criticize those who did the procedure.*";
P_HTM[491]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[492]="*Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has eight qualities, a procedure of demotion against him should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[493]="*Na pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposathaṃ ṭhapeti, na pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapeti, na savacanīyaṃ karoti, na anuvādaṃ paṭṭhapeti, na okāsaṃ kāreti, na codeti, na sāreti, na bhikkhūhi sampayojeti—**he doesn’t cancel the observance-day procedure of a regular monk; he doesn’t cancel the invitation procedure of a regular monk; he doesn’t speak to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him; he doesn’t make accusations against a regular monk; he doesn’t ask a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense; he doesn’t accuse a regular monk of an offense; he doesn’t remind a regular monk of an offense; he doesn’t associate inappropriately with other monks.”*";
P_HTM[494]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[495]="*Paṭippassambhetabbaaṭṭhārasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of eighteen on to be lifted is finished.*";
P_HTM[496]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**“And this is how it should be lifted.*";
P_HTM[497]="*Tena, bhikkhave, seyyasakena bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**After approaching the Sangha, the monk Seyyasaka should put his upper robes over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[498]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, saṅghena niyassakammakato sammā vattāmi, lomaṃ pātemi, netthāraṃ vattāmi, niyassassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācāmī’ti.**‘Venerables, the Sangha has done a legal procedure of demotion against me, but I have conducted myself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released. I ask for the legal procedure of demotion to be lifted.’*";
P_HTM[499]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbā.**And he should ask a second*";
P_HTM[500]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[501]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[502]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[503]="*Ayaṃ seyyasako bhikkhu saṅghena niyassakammakato sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, niyassassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācati.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of demotion against the monk Seyyasaka. He has conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now asks for the legal procedure of demotion to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[504]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho seyyasakassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ paṭippassambheyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should lift the legal procedure of demotion against the monk Seyyasaka.*";
P_HTM[505]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[506]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[507]="*Ayaṃ seyyasako bhikkhu saṅghena niyassakammakato sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, niyassassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācati.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of demotion against the monk Seyyasaka. He has conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now asks for the legal procedure of demotion to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[508]="*Saṅgho seyyasakassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ paṭippassambheti.**The Sangha lifts the legal procedure of demotion against the monk Seyyasaka.*";
P_HTM[509]="*Yassāyasmato khamati seyyasakassa bhikkhuno niyassassa kammassa paṭippassaddhi, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of lifting the legal procedure of demotion against the monk Seyyasaka should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[510]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[511]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—**For the second time I speak on this matter.*";
P_HTM[512]="*suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[513]="*Ayaṃ seyyasako bhikkhu saṅghena niyassakammakato sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, niyassassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācati.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of demotion against the monk Seyyasaka. He has conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now asks for the legal procedure of demotion to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[514]="*Saṅgho seyyasakassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ paṭippassambheti.**The Sangha lifts the legal procedure of demotion against the monk Seyyasaka.*";
P_HTM[515]="*Yassāyasmato khamati seyyasakassa bhikkhuno niyassassa kammassa paṭippassaddhi, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of lifting the legal procedure of demotion against the monk Seyyasaka should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[516]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[517]="*Tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—**For the third time I speak on this matter.*";
P_HTM[518]="*suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[519]="*Ayaṃ seyyasako bhikkhu saṅghena niyassakammakato sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, niyassassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācati.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of demotion against the monk Seyyasaka. He has conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now asks for the legal procedure of demotion to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[520]="*Saṅgho seyyasakassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ paṭippassambheti.**The Sangha lifts the legal procedure of demotion against the monk Seyyasaka.*";
P_HTM[521]="*Yassāyasmato khamati seyyasakassa bhikkhuno niyassassa kammassa paṭippassaddhi, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of lifting the legal procedure of demotion against the monk Seyyasaka should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[522]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[523]="*Paṭippassaddhaṃ saṅghena seyyasakassa bhikkhuno niyassakammaṃ.**The Sangha has lifted the legal procedure of demotion against the monk Seyyasaka.*";
P_HTM[524]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[525]="*Niyassakammaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ.**The second section on the legal procedure of demotion is finished.*";
P_HTM[526]="*3. Pabbājanīyakamma**3. The legal procedure of banishment*";
P_HTM[527]="*Tena kho pana samayena assajipunabbasukā nāma kīṭāgirismiṃ āvāsikā honti alajjino pāpabhikkhū.**At one time Assaji and Punabbasuka were the resident monks at Kīṭāgiri. They were bad and shameless,*";
P_HTM[528]="*Te evarūpaṃ anācāraṃ ācaranti—**and were misbehaving in many ways.*";
P_HTM[529]="*mālāvacchaṃ ropentipi ropāpentipi, siñcantipi siñcāpentipi, ocinantipi ocināpentipi, ganthentipi ganthāpentipi, ekatovaṇṭikamālaṃ karontipi kārāpentipi, ubhatovaṇṭikamālaṃ karontipi kārāpentipi, mañjarikaṃ karontipi kārāpentipi, vidhūtikaṃ karontipi kārāpentipi, vaṭaṃsakaṃ karontipi kārāpentipi, āveḷaṃ karontipi kārāpentipi, uracchadaṃ karontipi kārāpentipi.**They planted flowering trees, watered and plucked them, and then tied the flowers together. They made the flowers into garlands, garlands with stalks on one side and garlands with stalks on both sides. They made flower arrangements, wreaths, ornaments for the head, ornaments for the ears, and ornaments for the chest. And they had others do the same.*";
P_HTM[530]="*Te kulitthīnaṃ kuladhītānaṃ kulakumārīnaṃ kulasuṇhānaṃ kuladāsīnaṃ ekatovaṇṭikamālaṃ harantipi harāpentipi, ubhatovaṇṭikamālaṃ harantipi harāpentipi, mañjarikaṃ harantipi harāpentipi, vidhūtikaṃ harantipi harāpentipi, vaṭaṃsakaṃ harantipi harāpentipi, āveḷaṃ harantipi harāpentipi, uracchadaṃ harantipi harāpentipi.**They then took these things, or sent them, to the women, the daughters, the girls, the daughters-in-law, and the female slaves of good families.*";
P_HTM[531]="*Te kulitthīhi kuladhītāhi kulakumārīhi kulasuṇhāhi kuladāsīhi saddhiṃ ekabhājanepi bhuñjanti, ekathālakepi pivanti, ekāsanepi nisīdanti, ekamañcepi tuvaṭṭenti, ekattharaṇāpi tuvaṭṭenti, ekapāvuraṇāpi tuvaṭṭenti, ekattharaṇapāvuraṇāpi tuvaṭṭenti, vikālepi bhuñjanti, majjampi pivanti, mālāgandhavilepanampi dhārenti, naccantipi, gāyantipi, vādentipi, lāsentipi;**They ate from the same plates as these women and drank from the same vessels. They sat on the same seats as them, and they lay down on the same beds, on the same sheets, under the same covers, both on the same sheets and under the same covers. They ate at the wrong time, drank alcohol, and wore garlands, perfumes, and cosmetics. They danced, sang, played instruments, and performed.*";
P_HTM[532]="*naccantiyāpi naccanti, naccantiyāpi gāyanti, naccantiyāpi vādenti, naccantiyāpi lāsenti;**While the women were dancing, singing, playing instruments, and performing, so would they.*";
P_HTM[533]="*gāyantiyāpi naccanti, gāyantiyāpi gāyanti, gāyantiyāpi vādenti, gāyantiyāpi lāsenti;* **";
P_HTM[534]="*vādentiyāpi naccanti, vādentiyāpi gāyanti, vādentiyāpi vādenti, vādentiyāpi lāsenti;* **";
P_HTM[535]="*lāsentiyāpi naccanti, lāsentiyāpi gāyanti, lāsentiyāpi vādenti, lāsentiyāpi lāsenti;* **";
P_HTM[536]="*aṭṭhapadepi kīḷanti, dasapadepi kīḷanti, ākāsepi kīḷanti, parihārapathepi kīḷanti, santikāyapi kīḷanti, khalikāyapi kīḷanti, ghaṭikāyapi kīḷanti, salākahatthenapi kīḷanti, akkhenapi kīḷanti, paṅgacīrenapi kīḷanti, vaṅkakenapi kīḷanti, mokkhacikāyapi kīḷanti, ciṅgulakenapi kīḷanti, pattāḷhakenapi kīḷanti, rathakenapi kīḷanti, dhanukenapi kīḷanti, akkharikāyapi kīḷanti, manesikāyapi kīḷanti, yathāvajjenapi kīḷanti;**They played various games: eight-row checkers, ten-row checkers, imaginary checkers, hopscotch, spillikins, dice, tip-cat, painting with the hand, ball games, leaf flutes, toy plows, somersaults, toy windmills, toy measures, toy carriages, toy bows, letter guessing, thought guessing, mimicking deformities.*";
P_HTM[537]="*hatthismimpi sikkhanti, assasmimpi sikkhanti, rathasmimpi sikkhanti, dhanusmimpi sikkhanti, tharusmimpi sikkhanti;**They trained in elephant riding, in horsemanship, in carriage riding, in archery, in swordsmanship.*";
P_HTM[538]="*hatthissapi purato dhāvanti, assassapi purato dhāvanti, rathassapi purato dhāvantipi ādhāvantipi;**And they ran in front of elephants, in front of horses, and in front of carriages, and they ran backward and forward.*";
P_HTM[539]="*usseḷentipi, apphoṭentipi, nibbujjhantipi, muṭṭhīhipi yujjhanti;**They whistled, clapped their hands, wrestled, and boxed.*";
P_HTM[540]="*raṅgamajjhepi saṅghāṭiṃ pattharitvā naccakiṃ evaṃ vadanti—**They spread their outer robe on a stage and said to the dancing girls,*";
P_HTM[541]="*“idha, bhagini, naccassū”ti;**“Dance here, Sister,”*";
P_HTM[542]="*nalāṭikampi denti;**and they made gestures of approval.*";
P_HTM[543]="*vividhampi anācāraṃ ācaranti.**And they misbehaved in a variety of ways.*";
P_HTM[544]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu kāsīsu vassaṃvuṭṭho sāvatthiṃ gacchanto bhagavantaṃ dassanāya yena kīṭāgiri tadavasari.**Just then a monk who had completed the rains residence in Kāsī was on his way to visit the Buddha at Sāvatthī when he arrived at Kīṭāgiri.*";
P_HTM[545]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya kīṭāgiriṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi pāsādikena abhikkantena paṭikkantena ālokitena vilokitena samiñjitena pasāritena, okkhittacakkhu iriyāpathasampanno.**In the morning he robed up, took his bowl and robe, and entered Kīṭāgiri to collect almsfood. He was pleasing in his conduct: in going out and coming back, in looking ahead and looking aside, in bending and stretching his arms. His eyes were lowered, and he was perfect in deportment.*";
P_HTM[546]="*Manussā taṃ bhikkhuṃ passitvā evamāhaṃsu—**When people saw him, they said,*";
P_HTM[547]="*“kvāyaṃ abalabalo viya mandamando viya bhākuṭikabhākuṭiko viya?**“Whoʼs this, acting like a moron and always frowning?*";
P_HTM[548]="*Ko imassa upagatassa piṇḍakampi dassati?**Who will give almsfood to him?*";
P_HTM[549]="*Amhākaṃ pana ayyā assajipunabbasukā saṇhā sakhilā sukhasambhāsā mihitapubbaṅgamā ehisvāgatavādino abbhākuṭikā uttānamukhā pubbabhāsino.**Almsfood should instead be given to our Venerables Assaji and Punabbasuka, for they are gentle, congenial, pleasant to speak with, greeting one with a smile, welcoming, friendly, open, the first to speak.”*";
P_HTM[550]="*Tesaṃ kho nāma piṇḍo dātabbo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[551]="*Addasā kho aññataro upāsako taṃ bhikkhuṃ kīṭāgirismiṃ piṇḍāya carantaṃ;**A certain lay follower saw that monk walking for alms in Kīṭāgiri.*";
P_HTM[552]="*disvāna yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ abhivādetvā etadavoca—**He approached him, bowed, and said,*";
P_HTM[553]="*“api, bhante, piṇḍo labbhatī”ti?**“Venerable, have you received any almsfood?”*";
P_HTM[554]="*“Na kho, āvuso, piṇḍo labbhatī”ti.**“No, I haven’t.”*";
P_HTM[555]="*“Ehi, bhante, gharaṃ gamissāmā”ti.**“Come, let’s go to my house.”*";
P_HTM[556]="*Atha kho so upāsako taṃ bhikkhuṃ gharaṃ netvā bhojetvā etadavoca—**He took that monk to his house and gave him a meal.*";
P_HTM[557]="*“kahaṃ, bhante, ayyo gamissatī”ti?**He then said, “Where are you going, Venerable?”*";
P_HTM[558]="*“Sāvatthiṃ kho ahaṃ, āvuso, gamissāmi bhagavantaṃ dassanāyā”ti.**“I’m going to Sāvatthī to see the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[559]="*“Tena hi, bhante, mama vacanena bhagavato pāde sirasā vanda, evañca vadehi—**“Well then, would you please pay respect at the feet of the Buddha in my name and say,*";
P_HTM[560]="*‘duṭṭho, bhante, kīṭāgirismiṃ āvāso.**‘Venerable Sir, the monastery in Kīṭāgiri has been corrupted.*";
P_HTM[561]="*Assajipunabbasukā nāma kīṭāgirismiṃ āvāsikā alajjino pāpabhikkhū.**Assaji and Punabbasuka are the resident monks there. They are bad and shameless,*";
P_HTM[562]="*Te evarūpaṃ anācāraṃ ācaranti—**and are misbehaving in many ways.*";
P_HTM[563]="*mālāvacchaṃ ropentipi ropāpentipi, siñcantipi siñcāpentipi, ocinantipi ocināpentipi, ganthentipi ganthāpentipi, ekatovaṇṭikamālaṃ karontipi kārāpentipi, ubhatovaṇṭikamālaṃ karontipi kārāpentipi, mañjarikaṃ karontipi kārāpentipi, vidhūtikaṃ karontipi kārāpentipi, vaṭaṃsakaṃ karontipi kārāpentipi, āveḷaṃ karontipi kārāpentipi, uracchadaṃ karontipi kārāpentipi.**They plant flowering trees, water them …*";
P_HTM[564]="*Te kulitthīnaṃ kuladhītānaṃ kulakumārīnaṃ kulasuṇhānaṃ kuladāsīnaṃ ekatovaṇṭikamālaṃ harantipi harāpentipi, ubhatovaṇṭikamālaṃ harantipi harāpentipi, mañjarikaṃ harantipi harāpentipi, vidhūtikaṃ harantipi harāpentipi, vaṭaṃsakaṃ harantipi harāpentipi, āveḷaṃ harantipi harāpentipi, uracchadaṃ harantipi harāpentipi.* **";
P_HTM[565]="*Te kulitthīhi kuladhītāhi kulakumārīhi kulasuṇhāhi kuladāsīhi saddhiṃ ekabhājanepi bhuñjanti, ekathālakepi pivanti, ekāsanepi nisīdanti, ekamañcepi tuvaṭṭenti, ekattharaṇāpi tuvaṭṭenti, ekapāvuraṇāpi tuvaṭṭenti, ekattharaṇapāvuraṇāpi tuvaṭṭenti, vikālepi bhuñjanti, majjampi pivanti, mālāgandhavilepanampi dhārenti, naccantipi, gāyantipi, vādentipi, lāsentipi;* **";
P_HTM[566]="*naccantiyāpi naccanti, naccantiyāpi gāyanti, naccantiyāpi vādenti, naccantiyāpi lāsenti …pe…* **";
P_HTM[567]="*(cakkaṃ kātabbaṃ).* **";
P_HTM[568]="*Lāsentiyāpi naccanti, lāsentiyāpi gāyanti, lāsentiyāpi vādenti, lāsentiyāpi lāsenti;* **";
P_HTM[569]="*aṭṭhapadepi kīḷanti, dasapadepi kīḷanti, ākāsepi kīḷanti, parihārapathepi kīḷanti, santikāyapi kīḷanti, khalikāyapi kīḷanti, ghaṭikāyapi kīḷanti, salākahatthenapi kīḷanti, akkhenapi kīḷanti, paṅgacīrenapi kīḷanti, vaṅkakenapi kīḷanti, mokkhacikāyapi kīḷanti, ciṅgulakenapi kīḷanti, pattāḷhakenapi kīḷanti, rathakenapi kīḷanti, dhanukenapi kīḷanti, akkharikāyapi kīḷanti, manesikāyapi kīḷanti, yathāvajjenapi kīḷanti;* **";
P_HTM[570]="*hatthismimpi sikkhanti, assasmimpi sikkhanti, rathasmimpi sikkhanti, dhanusmimpi sikkhanti, tharusmimpi sikkhanti;* **";
P_HTM[571]="*hatthissapi purato dhāvanti, assassapi purato dhāvanti, rathassapi purato dhāvantipi ādhāvantipi;* **";
P_HTM[572]="*usseḷentipi, apphoṭentipi, nibbujjhantipi, muṭṭhīhipi yujjhanti;* **";
P_HTM[573]="*raṅgamajjhepi saṅghāṭiṃ pattharitvā naccakiṃ evaṃ vadanti—* **";
P_HTM[574]="*“idha, bhagini, naccassū”ti;* **";
P_HTM[575]="*nalāṭikampi denti;* **";
P_HTM[576]="*vividhampi anācāraṃ ācaranti.**And they misbehave in a variety of ways.*";
P_HTM[577]="*Yepi te, bhante, manussā pubbe saddhā ahesuṃ pasannā tepi etarahi assaddhā appasannā.**Those who previously had faith and confidence have now lost it,*";
P_HTM[578]="*Yānipi tāni saṅghassa pubbe dānapathāni tānipi etarahi upacchinnāni.**and thereʼs no longer any support for the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[579]="*Riñcanti pesalā bhikkhū, nivasanti pāpabhikkhū.**The good monks have left and the bad monks are staying on.*";
P_HTM[580]="*Sādhu, bhante, bhagavā kīṭāgiriṃ bhikkhū pahiṇeyya, yathāyaṃ kīṭāgirismiṃ āvāso saṇṭhaheyyā’”ti.**Sir, please send monks to stay at the monastery in Kīṭāgiri.’”*";
P_HTM[581]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho so bhikkhu tassa upāsakassa paṭissuṇitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā yena sāvatthi tena pakkāmi.**The monk consented, got up, and set out for Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[582]="*Anupubbena yena sāvatthi jetavanaṃ anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāmo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**When he eventually arrived, he went to the Buddha in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery. He bowed to the Buddha and sat down.*";
P_HTM[583]="*Āciṇṇaṃ kho panetaṃ buddhānaṃ bhagavantānaṃ āgantukehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ paṭisammodituṃ.**Since it is the custom for Buddhas to greet newly arrived monks,*";
P_HTM[584]="*Atha kho bhagavā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—**the Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[585]="*“kacci, bhikkhu, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyaṃ,**“I hope you are keeping well, monk, I hope you’re getting by.*";
P_HTM[586]="*kaccisi appakilamathena addhānaṃ āgato,**I hope you’re not tired from traveling.*";
P_HTM[587]="*kuto ca tvaṃ bhikkhu āgacchasī”ti?**And where have you come from?”*";
P_HTM[588]="*“Khamanīyaṃ, bhagavā, yāpanīyaṃ, bhagavā;**“I’m keeping well, Venerable Sir, I’m getting by.*";
P_HTM[589]="*appakilamathena ca ahaṃ, bhante, addhānaṃ āgato.**I’m not tired from traveling.”*";
P_HTM[590]="*Idhāhaṃ, bhante, kāsīsu vassaṃvuṭṭho sāvatthiṃ āgacchanto bhagavantaṃ dassanāya yena kīṭāgiri tadavasariṃ.**He then told the Buddha all that had happened at Kīṭāgiri,*";
P_HTM[591]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, bhante, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya kīṭāgiriṃ piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[592]="*Addasā kho maṃ, bhante, aññataro upāsako kīṭāgirismiṃ piṇḍāya carantaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[593]="*disvāna yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā etadavoca—* **";
P_HTM[594]="*‘api, bhante, piṇḍo labbhatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[595]="*‘Na kho, āvuso, piṇḍo labbhatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[596]="*‘Ehi, bhante, gharaṃ gamissāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[597]="*Atha kho, bhante, so upāsako maṃ gharaṃ netvā bhojetvā etadavoca—* **";
P_HTM[598]="*‘kahaṃ, bhante, ayyo gamissatī’ti?* **";
P_HTM[599]="*‘Sāvatthiṃ kho ahaṃ, āvuso, gamissāmi bhagavantaṃ dassanāyā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[600]="*‘Tena hi, bhante, mama vacanena bhagavato pāde sirasā vanda, evañca vadehi—* **";
P_HTM[601]="*“duṭṭho, bhante, kīṭāgirismiṃ āvāso.* **";
P_HTM[602]="*Assajipunabbasukā nāma kīṭāgirismiṃ āvāsikā alajjino pāpabhikkhū.* **";
P_HTM[603]="*Te evarūpaṃ anācāraṃ ācaranti—* **";
P_HTM[604]="*mālāvacchaṃ ropentipi ropāpentipi …pe…* **";
P_HTM[605]="*vividhampi anācāraṃ ācaranti.* **";
P_HTM[606]="*Yepi te, bhante, manussā pubbe saddhā ahesuṃ pasannā tepi etarahi assaddhā appasannā.* **";
P_HTM[607]="*Yānipi tāni saṅghassa pubbe dānapathāni tānipi etarahi upacchinnāni.* **";
P_HTM[608]="*Riñcanti pesalā bhikkhū, nivasanti pāpabhikkhū.* **";
P_HTM[609]="*Sādhu, bhante, bhagavā kīṭāgiriṃ bhikkhū pahiṇeyya, yathāyaṃ kīṭāgirismiṃ āvāso saṇṭhaheyyā”’ti.* **";
P_HTM[610]="*Tato ahaṃ, bhagavā, āgacchāmī”ti.**adding, “That’s where I’ve come from, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[611]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[612]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, assajipunabbasukā nāma kīṭāgirismiṃ āvāsikā alajjino pāpabhikkhū?**“Is it true, monks, that the bad and shameless monks Assaji and Punabbasuka are misbehaving in this way?*";
P_HTM[613]="*Te evarūpaṃ anācāraṃ ācaranti—* **";
P_HTM[614]="*mālāvacchaṃ ropentipi …pe…* **";
P_HTM[615]="*vividhampi anācāraṃ ācaranti?* **";
P_HTM[616]="*Yepi te manussā pubbe saddhā ahesuṃ pasannā tepi etarahi assaddhā appasannā?**And is it true that those people who previously had faith and confidence have now lost it,*";
P_HTM[617]="*Yānipi tāni saṅghassa pubbe dānapathāni tānipi etarahi upacchinnāni?**that there’s no longer any support for the Sangha,*";
P_HTM[618]="*Riñcanti pesalā bhikkhū, nivasanti pāpabhikkhū”ti?**and that the good monks have left and the bad monks are staying on?”*";
P_HTM[619]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[620]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—**The Buddha criticized them,*";
P_HTM[621]="*“ananucchavikaṃ …pe…**“It’s not suitable …*";
P_HTM[622]="*kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā evarūpaṃ anācāraṃ ācarissanti—**How can those foolish men misbehave in this way?*";
P_HTM[623]="*mālāvacchaṃ ropessantipi ropāpessantipi, siñcissantipi siñcāpessantipi, ocinissantipi ocināpessantipi, ganthessantipi ganthāpessantipi, ekatovaṇṭikamālaṃ karissantipi kārāpessantipi, ubhatovaṇṭikamālaṃ karissantipi kārāpessantipi, mañjarikaṃ karissantipi kārāpessantipi, vidhūtikaṃ karissantipi kārāpessantipi, vaṭaṃsakaṃ karissantipi kārāpessantipi, āveḷaṃ karissantipi kārāpessantipi, uracchadaṃ karissantipi kārāpessantipi.* **";
P_HTM[624]="*Te kulitthīnaṃ kuladhītānaṃ kulakumārīnaṃ kulasuṇhānaṃ kuladāsīnaṃ ekatovaṇṭikamālaṃ harissantipi harāpessantipi, ubhatovaṇṭikamālaṃ harissantipi harāpessantipi, mañjarikaṃ harissantipi harāpessantipi, vidhūtikaṃ harissantipi harāpessantipi, vaṭaṃsakaṃ harissantipi harāpessantipi, āveḷaṃ harissantipi harāpessantipi, uracchadaṃ harissantipi harāpessantipi.* **";
P_HTM[625]="*Te kulitthīhi kuladhītāhi kulakumārīhi kulasuṇhāhi kuladāsīhi saddhiṃ ekabhājanepi bhuñjissanti, ekathālakepi pivissanti, ekāsanepi nisīdissanti, ekamañcepi tuvaṭṭissanti, ekattharaṇāpi tuvaṭṭissanti, ekapāvuraṇāpi tuvaṭṭissanti, ekattharaṇapāvuraṇāpi tuvaṭṭissanti, vikālepi bhuñjissanti, majjampi pivissanti, mālāgandhavilepanampi dhāressanti, naccissantipi, gāyissantipi, vādessantipi, lāsessantipi;* **";
P_HTM[626]="*naccantiyāpi naccissanti, naccantiyāpi gāyissanti, naccantiyāpi vādessanti, naccantiyāpi lāsessanti;* **";
P_HTM[627]="*gāyantiyāpi naccissanti, gāyantiyāpi gāyissanti, gāyantiyāpi vādessanti, gāyantiyāpi lāsessanti;* **";
P_HTM[628]="*vādentiyāpi naccissanti, vādentiyāpi gāyissanti, vādentiyāpi vādessanti, vādentiyāpi lāsessanti;* **";
P_HTM[629]="*lāsentiyāpi naccissanti, lāsentiyāpi gāyissanti, lāsentiyāpi vādessanti, lāsentiyāpi lāsessanti;* **";
P_HTM[630]="*aṭṭhapadepi kīḷissanti, dasapadepi kīḷissanti, ākāsepi kīḷissanti, parihārapathepi kīḷissanti, santikāyapi kīḷissanti, khalikāyapi kīḷissanti, ghaṭikāyapi kīḷissanti, salākahatthenapi kīḷissanti, akkhenapi kīḷissanti, paṅgacīrenapi kīḷissanti, vaṅkakenapi kīḷissanti mokkhacikāyapi kīḷissanti, ciṅgulakenapi kīḷissanti, pattāḷhakenapi kīḷissanti, rathakenapi kīḷissanti, dhanukenapi kīḷissanti, akkharikāyapi kīḷissanti, manesikāyapi kīḷissanti, yathāvajjenapi kīḷissanti;* **";
P_HTM[631]="*hatthismimpi sikkhissanti, assasmimpi sikkhissanti, rathasmimpi sikkhissanti, dhanusmimpi sikkhissanti, tharusmimpi sikkhissanti;* **";
P_HTM[632]="*hatthissapi purato dhāvissanti, assassapi purato dhāvissanti, rathassapi purato dhāvissantipi ādhāvissantipi;* **";
P_HTM[633]="*usseḷessantipi, apphoṭessantipi, nibbujjhissantipi, muṭṭhīhipi yujjhissanti;* **";
P_HTM[634]="*raṅgamajjhepi saṅghāṭiṃ pattharitvā naccakiṃ evaṃ vakkhanti—* **";
P_HTM[635]="*‘idha, bhagini, naccassū’ti;* **";
P_HTM[636]="*nalāṭikampi dassanti;* **";
P_HTM[637]="*vividhampi anācāraṃ ācarissanti.* **";
P_HTM[638]="*(…) Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[639]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[640]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā sāriputtamoggallāne āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed Sāriputta and Moggallāna:*";
P_HTM[641]="*“gacchatha tumhe, sāriputtā, kīṭāgiriṃ gantvā assajipunabbasukānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ kīṭāgirismā pabbājanīyakammaṃ karotha, tumhākaṃ ete saddhivihārino”ti.**“Sāriputta, the two of you should go and do a legal procedure of banishing the monks Assaji and Punabbasuka from Kīṭāgiri. They are your students.”*";
P_HTM[642]="*“Kathaṃ mayaṃ, bhante, assajipunabbasukānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ kīṭāgirismā pabbājanīyakammaṃ karoma, caṇḍā te bhikkhū pharusā”ti?**“Sir, how can we do a procedure of banishing these monks from Kīṭāgiri? They are temperamental and harsh.”*";
P_HTM[643]="*“Tena hi tumhe, sāriputtā, bahukehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ gacchathā”ti.**“Well, take many monks.”*";
P_HTM[644]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho sāriputtamoggallānā bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes.”*";
P_HTM[645]="*“Evañca pana, bhikkhave, kātabbaṃ—**“And this is how it should be done.*";
P_HTM[646]="*paṭhamaṃ assajipunabbasukā bhikkhū codetabbā, codetvā sāretabbā, sāretvā āpattiṃ āropetabbā, āpattiṃ āropetvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**First you should accuse the monks Assaji and Punabbasuka. They should then be reminded of what they have done, before they are charged with an offense. A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[647]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[648]="*Ime assajipunabbasukā bhikkhū kuladūsakā pāpasamācārā.**These monks, Assaji and Punabbasuka, are corrupters of families and badly behaved.*";
P_HTM[649]="*Imesaṃ pāpakā samācārā dissanti ceva suyyanti ca.**Their bad behavior is seen and heard about,*";
P_HTM[650]="*Kulāni ca imehi duṭṭhāni dissanti ceva suyyanti ca.**and the families corrupted by them are seen and heard about.*";
P_HTM[651]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho assajipunabbasukānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ kīṭāgirismā pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya—**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should do a legal procedure of banishing them,*";
P_HTM[652]="*na assajipunabbasukehi bhikkhūhi kīṭāgirismiṃ vatthabbanti.**prohibiting the monks Assaji and Punabbasuka from staying at Kīṭāgiri.*";
P_HTM[653]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[654]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[655]="*Ime assajipunabbasukā bhikkhū kuladūsakā pāpasamācārā.**These monks, Assaji and Punabbasuka, are corrupters of families and badly behaved.*";
P_HTM[656]="*Imesaṃ pāpakā samācārā dissanti ceva suyyanti ca.**Their bad behavior is seen and heard about,*";
P_HTM[657]="*Kulāni ca imehi duṭṭhāni dissanti ceva suyyanti ca.**and the families corrupted by them are seen and heard about.*";
P_HTM[658]="*Saṅgho assajipunabbasukānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ kīṭāgirismā pabbājanīyakammaṃ karoti—**The Sangha is doing a legal procedure of banishing them,*";
P_HTM[659]="*na assajipunabbasukehi bhikkhūhi kīṭāgirismiṃ vatthabbanti.**prohibiting the monks Assaji and Punabbasuka from staying at Kīṭāgiri.*";
P_HTM[660]="*Yassāyasmato khamati assajipunabbasukānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ kīṭāgirismā pabbājanīyassa kammassa karaṇaṃ—na assajipunabbasukehi bhikkhūhi kīṭāgirismiṃ vatthabbanti, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of doing a legal procedure of banishing them, prohibiting the monks Assaji and Punabbasuka from staying at Kīṭāgiri, should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[661]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[662]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter …*";
P_HTM[663]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi.**For the third time I speak on this matter.*";
P_HTM[664]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[665]="*Ime assajipunabbasukā bhikkhū kuladūsakā pāpasamācārā.**These monks, Assaji and Punabbasuka, are corrupters of families and badly behaved.*";
P_HTM[666]="*Imesaṃ pāpakā samācārā dissanti ceva suyyanti ca.**Their bad behavior is seen and heard about,*";
P_HTM[667]="*Kulāni ca imehi duṭṭhāni dissanti ceva suyyanti ca.**and the families corrupted by them are seen and heard about.*";
P_HTM[668]="*Saṅgho assajipunabbasukānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ kīṭāgirismā pabbājanīyakammaṃ karoti—**The Sangha is doing a legal procedure of banishing them,*";
P_HTM[669]="*na assajipunabbasukehi bhikkhūhi kīṭāgirismiṃ vatthabbanti.**prohibiting the monks Assaji and Punabbasuka from staying at Kīṭāgiri.*";
P_HTM[670]="*Yassāyasmato khamati assajipunabbasukānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ kīṭāgirismā pabbājanīyassa kammassa karaṇaṃ—na assajipunabbasukehi bhikkhūhi kīṭāgirismiṃ vatthabbanti, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of doing a legal procedure of banishing them, prohibiting the monks Assaji and Punabbasuka from staying at Kīṭāgiri, should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[671]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[672]="*Kataṃ saṅghena assajipunabbasukānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ kīṭāgirismā pabbājanīyakammaṃ—**The Sangha has done the legal procedure of banishing Assaji and Punabbasuka,*";
P_HTM[673]="*na assajipunabbasukehi bhikkhūhi kīṭāgirismiṃ vatthabbanti.**prohibiting them from staying at Kīṭāgiri.*";
P_HTM[674]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[675]="*3.1. Adhammakammadvādasaka**3.1 The group of twelve on illegitimate legal procedures*";
P_HTM[676]="*“Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgataṃ pabbājanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.**“When a legal procedure of banishment has three qualities, it is illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[677]="*Asammukhā kataṃ hoti, appaṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, appaṭiññāya kataṃ hoti—**it is done in the absence of the accused, it is done without questioning the accused, it is done without the admission of the accused.*";
P_HTM[678]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ pabbājanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[679]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ pabbājanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.**When a procedure of banishment has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[680]="*Anāpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adesanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, desitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti …pe…**it is done against one who hasn’t committed any offense, it is done against one who has committed an offense that isn’t clearable by confession, it is done against one who has confessed their offense.*";
P_HTM[681]="*acodetvā kataṃ hoti, asāretvā kataṃ hoti, āpattiṃ anāropetvā kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of banishment has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having accused the person of their offense, it is done without having reminded the person of their offense, it is done without having charged the person with their offense.*";
P_HTM[682]="*asammukhā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of banishment has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done in the absence of the accused, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[683]="*appaṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of banishment has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without questioning the accused, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[684]="*appaṭiññāya kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of banishment has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without the admission of the accused, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[685]="*anāpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of banishment has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done against one who hasn’t committed any offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[686]="*adesanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of banishment has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done against one who has committed an offense that isn’t clearable by confession, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[687]="*desitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of banishment has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done against one who has confessed their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[688]="*acodetvā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of banishment has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having accused the person of their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[689]="*asāretvā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of banishment has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having reminded the person of their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[690]="*āpattiṃ anāropetvā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti—**When a procedure of banishment has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having charged the person with their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.”*";
P_HTM[691]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ pabbājanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[692]="*Adhammakammadvādasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of twelve on illegitimate legal procedures is finished.*";
P_HTM[693]="*3.2. Dhammakammadvādasaka**3.2 The group of twelve on legitimate legal procedures*";
P_HTM[694]="*Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgataṃ pabbājanīyakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.**“When a legal procedure of banishment has three qualities, it is legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[695]="*Sammukhā kataṃ hoti, paṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, paṭiññāya kataṃ hoti—**it is done in the presence of the accused, it is done with the questioning of the accused, it is done with the admission of the accused.*";
P_HTM[696]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ pabbājanīyakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[697]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ pabbājanīyakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.**When a procedure of banishment has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[698]="*Āpattiyā kataṃ hoti desanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti adesitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti …pe…**it is done against one who has committed an offense, it is done against one who has committed an offense that is clearable by confession, it is done against one who hasn’t confessed their offense.*";
P_HTM[699]="*codetvā kataṃ hoti, sāretvā kataṃ hoti, āpattiṃ āropetvā kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of banishment has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done after having accused the person of their offense, it is done after having reminded the person of their offense, it is done after having charged the person with their offense.*";
P_HTM[700]="*sammukhā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of banishment has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done in the presence of the accused, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[701]="*paṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of banishment has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done with the questioning of the accused, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[702]="*paṭiññāya kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of banishment has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done with the admission of the accused, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[703]="*āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of banishment has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done against one who has committed an offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[704]="*desanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of banishment has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done against one who has committed an offense that is clearable by confession, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[705]="*adesitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of banishment has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done against one who hasn’t confessed their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[706]="*codetvā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of banishment has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done after having accused the person of their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[707]="*sāretvā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of banishment has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done after having reminded the person of their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[708]="*āpattiṃ āropetvā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti—**When a procedure of banishment has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done after having charged the person with their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.”*";
P_HTM[709]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ pabbājanīyakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[710]="*Dhammakammadvādasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of twelve on legitimate legal procedures is finished.*";
P_HTM[711]="*3.3. Ākaṅkhamānacuddasaka**3.3 The group of fourteen on wishing*";
P_HTM[712]="*Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**“When a monk has three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a legal procedure of banishing him:*";
P_HTM[713]="*Bhaṇḍanakārako hoti kalahakārako vivādakārako bhassakārako saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako;**he is quarrelsome, argumentative, and a creator of legal issues in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[714]="*bālo hoti abyatto āpattibahulo anapadāno;**he is ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, incapable of determining whether he has committed an offense;*";
P_HTM[715]="*gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi—**he is constantly and improperly socializing with householders.*";
P_HTM[716]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[717]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**When a monk has another three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of banishing him:*";
P_HTM[718]="*Adhisīle sīlavipanno hoti, ajjhācāre ācāravipanno hoti, atidiṭṭhiyā diṭṭhivipanno hoti—**he has failed in the higher morality; he has failed in conduct; he has failed in view.*";
P_HTM[719]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[720]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**When a monk has another three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of banishing him:*";
P_HTM[721]="*Buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—**he disparages the Buddha; he disparages the Teaching; he disparages the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[722]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[723]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**“When a monk has another three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of banishing him:*";
P_HTM[724]="*Kāyikena davena samannāgato hoti, vācasikena davena samannāgato hoti, kāyikavācasikena davena samannāgato hoti—**his bodily conduct is frivolous; his verbal conduct is frivolous; his bodily and verbal conduct are frivolous.*";
P_HTM[725]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[726]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**When a monk has another three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of banishing him:*";
P_HTM[727]="*Kāyikena anācārena samannāgato hoti, vācasikena anācārena samannāgato hoti, kāyikavācasikena anācārena samannāgato hoti—**he is improperly behaved by body; he is improperly behaved by speech; he is improperly behaved by body and speech.*";
P_HTM[728]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[729]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**When a monk has another three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of banishing him:*";
P_HTM[730]="*Kāyikena upaghātikena samannāgato hoti, vācasikena upaghātikena samannāgato hoti, kāyikavācasikena upaghātikena samannāgato hoti—**his bodily conduct is harmful; his verbal conduct is harmful; his bodily and verbal conduct are harmful.*";
P_HTM[731]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[732]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**When a monk has another three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of banishing him:*";
P_HTM[733]="*Kāyikena micchājīvena samannāgato hoti, vācasikena micchājīvena samannāgato hoti, kāyikavācasikena micchājīvena samannāgato hoti—**he has wrong livelihood by body; he has wrong livelihood by speech; he has wrong livelihood by body and speech.*";
P_HTM[734]="*imehi, kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[735]="*Tiṇṇaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**“The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of banishment against three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[736]="*Eko bhaṇḍanakārako hoti kalahakārako vivādakārako bhassakārako saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako;**those who are quarrelsome, argumentative, and creators of legal issues in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[737]="*eko bālo hoti abyatto āpattibahulo anapadāno;**those who are ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, incapable of determining whether they have committed an offense;*";
P_HTM[738]="*eko gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi—**those who are constantly and improperly socializing with householders.*";
P_HTM[739]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[740]="*Aparesampi, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of banishment against another three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[741]="*Eko adhisīle sīlavipanno hoti, eko ajjhācāre ācāravipanno hoti, eko atidiṭṭhiyā diṭṭhivipanno hoti—**those who have failed in the higher morality; those who have failed in conduct; those who have failed in view.*";
P_HTM[742]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[743]="*Aparesampi, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of banishment against another three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[744]="*Eko buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, eko dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, eko saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—**those who disparage the Buddha; those who disparage the Teaching; those who disparage the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[745]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[746]="*Aparesampi, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**“The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of banishment against another three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[747]="*Eko kāyikena davena samannāgato hoti, eko vācasikena davena samannāgato hoti, eko kāyikavācasikena davena samannāgato hoti—**those who are frivolous in bodily conduct; those who are frivolous in verbal conduct; those who are frivolous in bodily and verbal conduct.*";
P_HTM[748]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[749]="*Aparesampi, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of banishment against another three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[750]="*Eko kāyikena anācārena samannāgato hoti, eko vācasikena anācārena samannāgato hoti, eko kāyikavācasikena anācārena samannāgato hoti—**those who are improperly behaved by body; those who are improperly behaved by speech; those who are improperly behaved by body and speech.*";
P_HTM[751]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[752]="*Aparesampi, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of banishment against another three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[753]="*Eko kāyikena upaghātikena samannāgato hoti, eko vācasikena upaghātikena samannāgato hoti, eko kāyikavācasikena upaghātikena samannāgato hoti—**those whose bodily conduct is harmful; those whose verbal conduct is harmful; those whose bodily and verbal conduct are harmful.*";
P_HTM[754]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[755]="*Aparesampi, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of banishment against another three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[756]="*Eko kāyikena micchājīvena samannāgato hoti, eko vācasikena micchājīvena samannāgato hoti, eko kāyikavācasikena micchājīvena samannāgato hoti—**those who have wrong livelihood by body; those who have wrong livelihood by speech; those who have wrong livelihood by body and speech.”*";
P_HTM[757]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pabbājanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[758]="*Ākaṅkhamānacuddasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of fourteen on wishing is finished.*";
P_HTM[759]="*3.4. Aṭṭhārasavatta**3.4 The eighteen kinds of conduct*";
P_HTM[760]="*Pabbājanīyakammakatena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā sammā vattitabbaṃ.**“A monk who has had a legal procedure of banishment done against himself should conduct himself properly.*";
P_HTM[761]="*Tatrāyaṃ sammāvattanā—**This is the proper conduct:*";
P_HTM[762]="*na upasampādetabbaṃ,**He should not give the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[763]="*na nissayo dātabbo,**He should not give formal support.*";
P_HTM[764]="*na sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo,**He should not have a novice monk attend on him.*";
P_HTM[765]="*na bhikkhunovādakasammuti sāditabbā,**He should not accept being appointed as an instructor of the nuns.*";
P_HTM[766]="*sammatenapi bhikkhuniyo na ovaditabbā.**Even if appointed, he should not instruct the nuns.*";
P_HTM[767]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena pabbājanīyakammaṃ kataṃ hoti sā āpatti na āpajjitabbā,**He should not commit the same offense as the offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of banishing him.*";
P_HTM[768]="*aññā vā tādisikā,**He should not commit an offense similar to the offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of banishing him.*";
P_HTM[769]="*tato vā pāpiṭṭhatarā;**He should not commit an offense worse than the offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of banishing him.*";
P_HTM[770]="*kammaṃ na garahitabbaṃ,**He should not criticize the procedure.*";
P_HTM[771]="*kammikā na garahitabbā.**He should not criticize those who did the procedure.*";
P_HTM[772]="*Na pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposatho ṭhapetabbo,**He should not cancel the observance-day procedure of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[773]="*na pavāraṇā ṭhapetabbā,**He should not cancel the invitation procedure of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[774]="*na savacanīyaṃ kātabbaṃ,**He should not speak to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him.*";
P_HTM[775]="*na anuvādo paṭṭhapetabbo,**He should not make accusations against a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[776]="*na okāso kāretabbo,**He should not ask a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense.*";
P_HTM[777]="*na codetabbo,**He should not accuse a regular monk of an offense.*";
P_HTM[778]="*na sāretabbo,**He should not remind a regular monk of an offense.*";
P_HTM[779]="*na bhikkhūhi sampayojetabban”ti.**He should not associate inappropriately with other monks.”*";
P_HTM[780]="*Pabbājanīyakamme aṭṭhārasavattaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The eighteen kinds of conduct in regard to the legal procedure of banishment are finished.*";
P_HTM[781]="*Atha kho sāriputtamoggallānappamukho bhikkhusaṅgho kīṭāgiriṃ gantvā assajipunabbasukānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ kīṭāgirismā pabbājanīyakammaṃ akāsi—**Soon afterwards a sangha of monks, headed by Sāriputta and Moggallāna, went to Kīṭāgiri and did the legal procedure of banishing the monks Assaji and Punabbasuka,*";
P_HTM[782]="*na assajipunabbasukehi bhikkhūhi kīṭāgirismiṃ vatthabbanti.**prohibiting them from staying at Kīṭāgiri.*";
P_HTM[783]="*Te saṅghena pabbājanīyakammakatā na sammā vattanti, na lomaṃ pātenti, na netthāraṃ vattanti;**After the Sangha had done the procedure, those monks did not conduct themselves properly or suitably so as to deserve to be released,*";
P_HTM[784]="*na bhikkhū khamāpenti, akkosanti, paribhāsanti;**nor did they ask the monks for forgiveness. Instead they abused and reviled them,*";
P_HTM[785]="*chandagāmitā dosagāmitā mohagāmitā bhayagāmitā pāpenti;**and they slandered them as acting from desire, ill will, confusion, and fear.*";
P_HTM[786]="*pakkamantipi, vibbhamantipi.**And they left and they disrobed.*";
P_HTM[787]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[788]="*“kathañhi nāma assajipunabbasukā bhikkhū saṅghena pabbājanīyakammakatā na sammā vattissanti, na lomaṃ pātessanti, na netthāraṃ vattissanti;**“How can these monks act like this when the Sangha has done a legal procedure of banishing them?”*";
P_HTM[789]="*na bhikkhū khamāpessanti, akkosissanti, paribhāsissanti;* **";
P_HTM[790]="*chandagāmitā dosagāmitā mohagāmitā bhayagāmitā pāpessanti;* **";
P_HTM[791]="*pakkamissantipi, vibbhamissantipī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[792]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[793]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[794]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, assajipunabbasukā bhikkhū saṅghena pabbājanīyakammakatā na sammā vattanti, na lomaṃ pātenti, na netthāraṃ vattanti;**“Is it true, monks, that the monks Assaji and Punabbasuka acted in this way?”*";
P_HTM[795]="*na bhikkhū khamāpenti, akkosanti, paribhāsanti;* **";
P_HTM[796]="*chandagāmitā dosagāmitā mohagāmitā bhayagāmitā pāpenti;* **";
P_HTM[797]="*pakkamantipi, vibbhamantipī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[798]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[799]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[800]="*“ananucchavikaṃ …pe…**“It’s not suitable …*";
P_HTM[801]="*kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā saṅghena pabbājanīyakammakatā na sammā vattissanti, na lomaṃ pātessanti, na netthāraṃ vattissanti;**How could these foolish men act in this way?*";
P_HTM[802]="*na bhikkhū khamāpessanti, akkosissanti, paribhāsissanti;* **";
P_HTM[803]="*chandagāmitā dosagāmitā mohagāmitā bhayagāmitā pāpessanti;* **";
P_HTM[804]="*pakkamissantipi, vibbhamissantipi.* **";
P_HTM[805]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[806]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**and after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[807]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[808]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho pabbājanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetu.**“Well then, don’t lift that legal procedure of banishment.*";
P_HTM[809]="*3.5. Nappaṭippassambhetabbaaṭṭhārasaka**3.5 The group of eighteen on not to be lifted*";
P_HTM[810]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno pabbājanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**“When a monk has five qualities, a legal procedure of banishing him should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[811]="*Upasampādeti, nissayaṃ deti, sāmaṇeraṃ upaṭṭhāpeti, bhikkhunovādakasammutiṃ sādiyati, sammatopi bhikkhuniyo ovadati—**he gives the full ordination; he gives formal support; he has a novice monk attend on him; he accepts being appointed as an instructor of the nuns; he instructs the nuns, whether appointed or not.*";
P_HTM[812]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno pabbājanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[813]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno pabbājanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of banishing him should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[814]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena pabbājanīyakammaṃ kataṃ hoti taṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati, aññaṃ vā tādisikaṃ, tato vā pāpiṭṭhataraṃ;**he commits the same offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of banishing him; he commits an offense similar to the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of banishing him; he commits an offense worse than the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of banishing him;*";
P_HTM[815]="*kammaṃ garahati, kammike garahati—**he criticizes the procedure; he criticizes those who did the procedure.*";
P_HTM[816]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno pabbājanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[817]="*Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno pabbājanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has eight qualities, a procedure of banishing him should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[818]="*Pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposathaṃ ṭhapeti, pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapeti, savacanīyaṃ karoti, anuvādaṃ paṭṭhapeti, okāsaṃ kāreti, codeti, sāreti, bhikkhūhi sampayojeti—**he cancels the observance-day procedure of a regular monk; he cancels the invitation procedure of a regular monk; he speaks to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him; he makes accusations against a regular monk; he asks a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense; he accuses a regular monk of an offense; he reminds a regular monk of an offense; he associates inappropriately with other monks.”*";
P_HTM[819]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno pabbājanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[820]="*Pabbājanīyakamme nappaṭippassambhetabbaaṭṭhārasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of eighteen on not to be lifted is finished.*";
P_HTM[821]="*3.6. Paṭippassambhetabbaaṭṭhārasaka**3.6 The group of eighteen on to be lifted*";
P_HTM[822]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno pabbājanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**“When a monk has five qualities, a legal procedure of banishing him should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[823]="*Na upasampādeti, na nissayaṃ deti, na sāmaṇeraṃ upaṭṭhāpeti, na bhikkhunovādakasammutiṃ sādiyati, sammatopi bhikkhuniyo na ovadati—**he does not give the full ordination; he does not give formal support; he does not have a novice monk attend on him; he does not accept being appointed as an instructor of the nuns; he does not instruct the nuns, whether appointed or not.*";
P_HTM[824]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno pabbājanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[825]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno pabbājanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of banishing him should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[826]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena pabbājanīyakammaṃ kataṃ hoti taṃ āpattiṃ na āpajjati, aññaṃ vā tādisikaṃ, tato vā pāpiṭṭhataraṃ;**he doesn’t commit the same offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of banishing him; he doesn’t commit an offense similar to the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of banishing him; he doesn’t commit an offense worse than the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of banishing him;*";
P_HTM[827]="*kammaṃ na garahati, kammike na garahati—**he doesn’t criticize the procedure; he doesn’t criticize those who did the procedure.*";
P_HTM[828]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno pabbājanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[829]="*Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno pabbājanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has eight qualities, a procedure of banishing him should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[830]="*Na pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposathaṃ ṭhapeti, na pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapeti, na savacanīyaṃ karoti, na anuvādaṃ paṭṭhapeti, na okāsaṃ kāreti, na codeti, na sāreti, na bhikkhūhi sampayojeti—**he doesn’t cancel the observance-day procedure of a regular monk; he doesn’t cancel the invitation procedure of a regular monk; he doesn’t speak to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him; he doesn’t make accusations against a regular monk; he doesn’t ask a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense; he doesn’t accuse a regular monk of an offense; he doesn’t remind a regular monk of an offense; he doesn’t associate inappropriately with other monks.”*";
P_HTM[831]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno pabbājanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[832]="*Pabbājanīyakamme paṭippassambhetabbaaṭṭhārasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of eighteen on to be lifted is finished.*";
P_HTM[833]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**“And this is how it should be lifted.*";
P_HTM[834]="*Tena, bhikkhave, pabbājanīyakammakatena bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**After approaching the Sangha, the monk who has had a legal procedure of banishment done against himself should put his upper robes over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[835]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, saṅghena pabbājanīyakammakato sammā vattāmi, lomaṃ pātemi, netthāraṃ vattāmi, pabbājanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācāmī’ti.**‘Venerables, the Sangha has done a legal procedure of banishing me, but I have conducted myself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released. I ask for the legal procedure of banishment to be lifted.’*";
P_HTM[836]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbā.**And he should ask a second*";
P_HTM[837]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[838]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[839]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[840]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu saṅghena pabbājanīyakammakato sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, pabbājanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācati.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of banishing monk so-and-so. He has conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now asks for the legal procedure of banishment to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[841]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno pabbājanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambheyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should lift the legal procedure of banishing him.*";
P_HTM[842]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[843]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[844]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu saṅghena pabbājanīyakammakato sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, pabbājanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācati.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of banishing monk so-and-so. He has conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now asks for the legal procedure of banishment to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[845]="*Saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno pabbājanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambheti.**The Sangha lifts the legal procedure of banishing him.*";
P_HTM[846]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno pabbājanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhi, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of lifting the legal procedure of banishing monk so-and-so should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[847]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[848]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[849]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi.**For the third time I speak on this matter.*";
P_HTM[850]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[851]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu saṅghena pabbājanīyakammakato sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, pabbājanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācati.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of banishing monk so-and-so. He has conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now asks for the legal procedure of banishment to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[852]="*Saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno pabbājanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambheti.**The Sangha lifts the legal procedure of banishing him.*";
P_HTM[853]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno pabbājanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhi, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of lifting the legal procedure of banishing monk so-and-so should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[854]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[855]="*Paṭippassaddhaṃ saṅghena itthannāmassa bhikkhuno pabbājanīyakammaṃ.**The Sangha has lifted the legal procedure of banishing monk so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[856]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[857]="*Pabbājanīyakammaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ.**The second section on the legal procedure of banishment is finished.*";
P_HTM[858]="*4. Paṭisāraṇīyakamma**4. The legal procedure of reconciliation*";
P_HTM[859]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā sudhammo macchikāsaṇḍe cittassa gahapatino āvāsiko hoti, navakammiko dhuvabhattiko.**At one time Venerable Sudhamma was the resident monk at the householder Citta’s monastery at Macchikāsaṇḍa. He was in charge of the building work and received a regular supply of food.*";
P_HTM[860]="*Yadā citto gahapati saṅghaṃ vā gaṇaṃ vā puggalaṃ vā nimantetukāmo hoti tadā na āyasmantaṃ sudhammaṃ anapaloketvā saṅghaṃ vā gaṇaṃ vā puggalaṃ vā nimanteti.**When Citta wanted to invite the Sangha, a group of monks, or an individual monk, he would not do so without getting permission from Sudhamma.*";
P_HTM[861]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā therā bhikkhū, āyasmā ca sāriputto, āyasmā ca mahāmoggallāno, āyasmā ca mahākaccāno, āyasmā ca mahākoṭṭhiko, āyasmā ca mahākappino, āyasmā ca mahācundo, āyasmā ca anuruddho, āyasmā ca revato, āyasmā ca upāli, āyasmā ca ānando, āyasmā ca rāhulo, kāsīsu cārikaṃ caramānā yena macchikāsaṇḍo tadavasaruṃ.**On one occasion a number of senior monks—Venerable Sāriputta, Venerable Mahāmoggallāna, Venerable Mahākaccāna, Venerable Mahākoṭṭhika, Venerable Mahākappina, Venerable Mahācunda, Venerable Anuruddha, Venerable Revata, Venerable Upāli, Venerable Ānanda, Venerable Rāhula—were wandering in Kāsī, when they arrived at Macchikāsaṇḍa.*";
P_HTM[862]="*Assosi kho citto gahapati therā kira bhikkhū macchikāsaṇḍaṃ anuppattāti.**When Citta heard that they had arrived,*";
P_HTM[863]="*Atha kho citto gahapati yena therā bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā there bhikkhū abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**he went to them, bowed, and sat down.*";
P_HTM[864]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho cittaṃ gahapatiṃ āyasmā sāriputto dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi.**After Sāriputta had instructed, inspired, and gladdened Citta with a teaching,*";
P_HTM[865]="*Atha kho citto gahapati āyasmatā sāriputtena dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito there bhikkhū etadavoca—**Citta said,*";
P_HTM[866]="*“adhivāsentu me, bhante, therā svātanāya āgantukabhattan”ti.**“Venerables, please accept a meal for new arrivals from me tomorrow.”*";
P_HTM[867]="*Adhivāsesuṃ kho therā bhikkhū tuṇhībhāvena.**And they accepted by remaining silent.*";
P_HTM[868]="*Atha kho citto gahapati therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā there bhikkhū abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā yenāyasmā sudhammo tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ sudhammaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi.**When he knew that they had accepted, Citta got up from his seat, bowed down, circumambulated them with his right side toward them, and went to Sudhamma. He bowed to him*";
P_HTM[869]="*Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho citto gahapati āyasmantaṃ sudhammaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[870]="*“adhivāsetu me, bhante, ayyo sudhammo svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ therehī”ti.**“Venerable, please accept tomorrow’s meal from me together with the senior monks.”*";
P_HTM[871]="*Atha kho āyasmā sudhammo—**Sudhamma thought,*";
P_HTM[872]="*“pubbe khvāyaṃ citto gahapati yadā saṅghaṃ vā gaṇaṃ vā puggalaṃ vā nimantetukāmo na maṃ anapaloketvā saṅghaṃ vā gaṇaṃ vā puggalaṃ vā nimanteti;**“Previously when Citta wanted to invite the Sangha, a group of monks, or an individual monk, he would not do so without getting my permission.*";
P_HTM[873]="*sodāni maṃ anapaloketvā there bhikkhū nimantesi;**But now he has invited the senior monks without my permission.*";
P_HTM[874]="*duṭṭhodānāyaṃ citto gahapati anapekkho virattarūpo mayī”ti cittaṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca—**He’s been corrupted, this Citta. He’s uninterested and has no affection for me.” He said to Citta,*";
P_HTM[875]="*“alaṃ, gahapati, nādhivāsemī”ti.**“There’s no need; I won’t accept.”*";
P_HTM[876]="*Dutiyampi kho …pe…**Citta asked him a second*";
P_HTM[877]="*tatiyampi kho citto gahapati āyasmantaṃ sudhammaṃ etadavoca—**and a third time,*";
P_HTM[878]="*“adhivāsetu me, bhante, ayyo sudhammo svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ therehī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[879]="*“Alaṃ, gahapati, nādhivāsemī”ti.**but got the same reply.*";
P_HTM[880]="*Atha kho citto gahapati—**He thought,*";
P_HTM[881]="*“kiṃ me karissati ayyo sudhammo adhivāsento vā anadhivāsento vā”ti āyasmantaṃ sudhammaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**“What difference does it make to me whether Sudhamma accepts or not?” He then bowed down, circumambulated Sudhamma with his right side toward him, and left.*";
P_HTM[882]="*Atha kho citto gahapati tassā rattiyā accayena therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpesi.**The following morning Citta prepared various kinds of fine food for the senior monks.*";
P_HTM[883]="*Atha kho āyasmā sudhammo—**Sudhamma thought,*";
P_HTM[884]="*“yannūnāhaṃ cittassa gahapatino therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ paṭiyattaṃ passeyyan”ti pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena cittassa gahapatino nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**“Why don’t I go and see what Citta has prepared for the senior monks?” He then robed up, took his bowl and robe, and went to Citta’s house, where he sat down on the prepared seat.*";
P_HTM[885]="*Atha kho citto gahapati yenāyasmā sudhammo tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ sudhammaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Citta approached Sudhamma, bowed, and sat down.*";
P_HTM[886]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho cittaṃ gahapatiṃ āyasmā sudhammo etadavoca—**And Sudhamma said to him,*";
P_HTM[887]="*“pahūtaṃ kho te idaṃ, gahapati, khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyattaṃ;**“You have prepared many kinds of food.*";
P_HTM[888]="*ekā ca kho idha natthi yadidaṃ tilasaṅguḷikā”ti.**But there’s one that’s missing: sesame cookies.”*";
P_HTM[889]="*“Bahumhi vata, bhante, ratane buddhavacane vijjamāne ayyena sudhammena yadeva kiñci bhāsitaṃ yadidaṃ tilasaṅguḷikāti.**“When there are so many jewels in the word of the Buddha, Sir, you speak of sesame cookies.*";
P_HTM[890]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhante, dakkhiṇāpathakā vāṇijā puratthimaṃ janapadaṃ agamaṃsu vāṇijjāya.**In the past there were some traders from the south who went to an eastern country to trade.*";
P_HTM[891]="*Te tato kukkuṭiṃ ānesuṃ.**From there they brought back a hen.*";
P_HTM[892]="*Atha kho sā, bhante, kukkuṭī kākena saddhiṃ saṃvāsaṃ kappesi.**That hen mated with a crow*";
P_HTM[893]="*Sā potakaṃ janesi.**and because of that she had a chick.*";
P_HTM[894]="*Yadā kho so, bhante, kukkuṭapotako kākavassaṃ vassitukāmo hoti, kākakukkuṭīti vassati;**When that chick wanted to caw like a crow, it cried, ‘caw-ca-doodle-doo.’*";
P_HTM[895]="*yadā kukkuṭivassaṃ vassitukāmo hoti, kukkuṭikākāti vassati.**And when that chick wanted to crow like a rooster, it cried, ‘cock-a-doodle-caw.’*";
P_HTM[896]="*Evameva kho, bhante, bahumhi ratane buddhavacane vijjamāne ayyena sudhammena yadeva kiñci bhāsitaṃ yadidaṃ tilasaṅguḷikā”ti.**In the same way, when there are so many jewels in the word of the Buddha, you speak of sesame cookies.”*";
P_HTM[897]="*“Akkosasi maṃ tvaṃ, gahapati, paribhāsasi maṃ tvaṃ, gahapati.**“Householder, you’re abusing and insulting me.*";
P_HTM[898]="*Eso te, gahapati, āvāso, pakkamissāmī”ti.**I will leave your monastery.”*";
P_HTM[899]="*“Nāhaṃ, bhante, ayyaṃ sudhammaṃ akkosāmi, paribhāsāmi.**“I’m not abusing and insulting you.*";
P_HTM[900]="*Vasatu, bhante, ayyo sudhammo macchikāsaṇḍe.**Please stay at Macchikāsaṇḍa.*";
P_HTM[901]="*Ramaṇīyaṃ ambāṭakavanaṃ.**The mango grove is delightful.*";
P_HTM[902]="*Ahaṃ ayyassa sudhammassa ussukkaṃ karissāmi, cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānan”ti.**I’ll do my best to supply you with robes, almsfood, a dwelling, and medicines.”*";
P_HTM[903]="*Dutiyampi kho …pe…**Sudhamma repeated what he had said a second time and Citta responded as before.*";
P_HTM[904]="*tatiyampi kho āyasmā sudhammo cittaṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca—**When Sudhamma repeated it a third time,*";
P_HTM[905]="*“akkosasi maṃ tvaṃ, gahapati, paribhāsasi maṃ tvaṃ, gahapati.* **";
P_HTM[906]="*Eso te, gahapati, āvāso, pakkamissāmī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[907]="*“Kahaṃ, bhante, ayyo sudhammo gamissatī”ti?**Citta said, “Where will you go?”*";
P_HTM[908]="*“Sāvatthiṃ kho ahaṃ, gahapati, gamissāmi bhagavantaṃ dassanāyā”ti.**“I’ll go to Sāvatthī to visit the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[909]="*“Tena hi, bhante, yañca attanā bhaṇitaṃ, yañca mayā bhaṇitaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato ārocehi.**“Well then, please tell the Buddha of our entire conversation.*";
P_HTM[910]="*Anacchariyaṃ kho panetaṃ, bhante, yaṃ ayyo sudhammo punadeva macchikāsaṇḍaṃ paccāgaccheyyā”ti.**And I would not be surprised if you returned to Macchikāsaṇḍa.”*";
P_HTM[911]="*Atha kho āyasmā sudhammo senāsanaṃ saṃsāmetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena sāvatthi tena pakkāmi.**Sudhamma put his dwelling in order, took his bowl and robe, and left for Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[912]="*Anupubbena yena sāvatthi jetavanaṃ anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāmo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**When he eventually arrived, he went to the Buddha in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery. He bowed to the Buddha, sat down,*";
P_HTM[913]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sudhammo yañca attanā bhaṇitaṃ yañca cittena gahapatinā bhaṇitaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato ārocesi.**and told him about the conversation he had had with Citta.*";
P_HTM[914]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—**The Buddha rebuked him,*";
P_HTM[915]="*“ananucchavikaṃ, moghapurisa, ananulomikaṃ appatirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ akaraṇīyaṃ.**“It’s not suitable, foolish man, it’s not proper, it’s not worthy of a monastic, it’s not allowable, it’s not to be done.*";
P_HTM[916]="*Kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, cittaṃ gahapatiṃ saddhaṃ pasannaṃ dāyakaṃ kārakaṃ saṅghupaṭṭhākaṃ hīnena khuṃsessasi, hīnena vambhessasi?**How can you demean and insult Citta, who has faith and confidence, who is a donor and benefactor, and a supporter of the Sangha?*";
P_HTM[917]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[918]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after rebuking him …*";
P_HTM[919]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[920]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho sudhammassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ karotu—**“Well then, do a legal procedure of reconciliation against the monk Sudhamma,*";
P_HTM[921]="*citto te gahapati khamāpetabboti.**instructing him to ask Citta for forgiveness.*";
P_HTM[922]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, kātabbaṃ—**And it should be done like this.*";
P_HTM[923]="*paṭhamaṃ sudhammo bhikkhu codetabbo, codetvā sāretabbo, sāretvā āpattiṃ āropetabbo, āpattiṃ āropetvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**First you should accuse the monk Sudhamma. He should then be reminded of what he has done, before he is charged with an offense. A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[924]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[925]="*Ayaṃ sudhammo bhikkhu cittaṃ gahapatiṃ saddhaṃ pasannaṃ dāyakaṃ kārakaṃ saṅghupaṭṭhākaṃ hīnena khuṃseti, hīnena vambheti.**The monk Sudhamma has demeaned and insulted the householder Citta, who has faith and confidence, who is a donor and benefactor, and a supporter of the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[926]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho sudhammassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ kareyya—**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should do a legal procedure of reconciliation against the monk Sudhamma,*";
P_HTM[927]="*citto te gahapati khamāpetabboti.**instructing him to ask Citta for forgiveness.*";
P_HTM[928]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[929]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[930]="*Ayaṃ sudhammo bhikkhu cittaṃ gahapatiṃ saddhaṃ pasannaṃ dāyakaṃ kārakaṃ saṅghupaṭṭhākaṃ hīnena khuṃseti, hīnena vambheti.**The monk Sudhamma has demeaned and insulted the householder Citta, who has faith and confidence, who is a donor and benefactor, and a supporter of the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[931]="*Saṅgho sudhammassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ karoti—**The Sangha is doing a legal procedure of reconciliation against the monk Sudhamma,*";
P_HTM[932]="*citto te gahapati khamāpetabboti.**instructing him to ask Citta for forgiveness.*";
P_HTM[933]="*Yassāyasmato khamati sudhammassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyassa kammassa karaṇaṃ—citto te gahapati khamāpetabboti, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of doing a legal procedure of reconciliation against the monk Sudhamma, instructing him to ask Citta for forgiveness, should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[934]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[935]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter …*";
P_HTM[936]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—**For the third time I speak on this matter.*";
P_HTM[937]="*suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[938]="*Ayaṃ sudhammo bhikkhu cittaṃ gahapatiṃ saddhaṃ pasannaṃ dāyakaṃ kārakaṃ saṅghupaṭṭhākaṃ hīnena khuṃseti, hīnena vambheti.**The monk Sudhamma has demeaned and insulted the householder Citta, who has faith and confidence, who is a donor and benefactor, and a supporter of the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[939]="*Saṅgho sudhammassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ karoti—**The Sangha is doing a legal procedure of reconciliation against the monk Sudhamma,*";
P_HTM[940]="*citto te gahapati khamāpetabboti.**instructing him to ask Citta for forgiveness.*";
P_HTM[941]="*Yassāyasmato khamati sudhammassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyassa kammassa karaṇaṃ—citto te gahapati khamāpetabboti, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of doing a legal procedure of reconciliation against the monk Sudhamma, instructing him to ask Citta for forgiveness, should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[942]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[943]="*Kataṃ saṅghena sudhammassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ—**The Sangha has done the legal procedure of reconciliation against the monk Sudhamma,*";
P_HTM[944]="*citto te gahapati khamāpetabboti.**instructing him to ask Citta for forgiveness.*";
P_HTM[945]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[946]="*4.1. Adhammakammadvādasaka**4.1 The group of twelve on illegitimate legal procedures*";
P_HTM[947]="*Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgataṃ paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.**“When a legal procedure of reconciliation has three qualities, it is illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[948]="*Asammukhā kataṃ hoti, appaṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, appaṭiññāya kataṃ hoti—**it is done in the absence of the accused, it is done without questioning the accused, it is done without the admission of the accused.*";
P_HTM[949]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[950]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.**When a procedure of reconciliation has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[951]="*Anāpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adesanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, desitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti …pe…**it is done against one who hasn’t committed any offense, it is done against one who has committed an offense that isn’t clearable by confession, it is done against one who has confessed their offense.*";
P_HTM[952]="*acodetvā kataṃ hoti, asāretvā kataṃ hoti, āpattiṃ anāropetvā kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of reconciliation has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having accused the person of their offense, it is done without having reminded the person of their offense, it is done without having charged the person with their offense.*";
P_HTM[953]="*asammukhā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of reconciliation has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done in the absence of the accused, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[954]="*appaṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of reconciliation has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without questioning the accused, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[955]="*appaṭiññāya kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of reconciliation has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without the admission of the accused, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[956]="*anāpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of reconciliation has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done against one who hasn’t committed any offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[957]="*adesanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of reconciliation has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done against one who has committed an offense that isn’t clearable by confession, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[958]="*desitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of reconciliation has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done against one who has confessed their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[959]="*acodetvā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of reconciliation has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having accused the person of their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[960]="*asāretvā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of reconciliation has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having reminded the person of their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[961]="*āpattiṃ anāropetvā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti—**When a procedure of reconciliation has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having charged the person with their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.”*";
P_HTM[962]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[963]="*Paṭisāraṇīyakamme adhammakammadvādasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of twelve on illegitimate legal procedures of reconciliation is finished.*";
P_HTM[964]="*4.2. Dhammakammadvādasaka**4.2 The group of twelve on legitimate legal procedures*";
P_HTM[965]="*Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgataṃ paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.**“When a legal procedure of reconciliation has three qualities, it is legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[966]="*Sammukhā kataṃ hoti, paṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, paṭiññāya kataṃ hoti—**it is done in the presence of the accused, it is done with the questioning of the accused, it is done with the admission of the accused.*";
P_HTM[967]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[968]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.**When a procedure of reconciliation has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[969]="*Āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, desanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adesitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti …pe…**it is done against one who has committed an offense, it is done against one who has committed an offense that is clearable by confession, it is done against one who hasn’t confessed their offense.*";
P_HTM[970]="*codetvā kataṃ hoti, sāretvā kataṃ hoti, āpattiṃ āropetvā kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of reconciliation has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done after having accused the person of their offense, it is done after having reminded the person of their offense, it is done after having charged the person with their offense.*";
P_HTM[971]="*sammukhā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of reconciliation has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done in the presence of the accused, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[972]="*paṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of reconciliation has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done with the questioning of the accused, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[973]="*paṭiññāya kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of reconciliation has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done with the admission of the accused, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[974]="*āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of reconciliation has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done against one who has committed an offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[975]="*desanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of reconciliation has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done against one who has committed an offense that is clearable by confession, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[976]="*adesitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of reconciliation has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done against one who hasn’t confessed their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[977]="*codetvā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of reconciliation has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done after having accused the person of their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[978]="*sāretvā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of reconciliation has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done after having reminded the person of their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[979]="*āpattiṃ āropetvā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti—**When a procedure of reconciliation has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done after having charged the person with their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.”*";
P_HTM[980]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[981]="*Paṭisāraṇīyakamme dhammakammadvādasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of twelve on legitimate legal procedures of reconciliation is finished.*";
P_HTM[982]="*4.3. Ākaṅkhamānacatukka**4.3 The group of four on wishing*";
P_HTM[983]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ kareyya.**“When a monk has five qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a legal procedure of reconciliation against him:*";
P_HTM[984]="*Gihīnaṃ alābhāya parisakkati, gihīnaṃ anatthāya parisakkati, gihīnaṃ anāvāsāya parisakkati, gihī akkosati paribhāsati, gihī gihīhi bhedeti—**he is trying to stop householders from acquiring material gain; he is trying to harm householders; he is trying to get householders to lose their place of residence; he abuses and reviles householders; he causes division between householders.*";
P_HTM[985]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[986]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ kareyya.**When a monk has another five qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of reconciliation against him:*";
P_HTM[987]="*Gihīnaṃ buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, gihīnaṃ dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, gihīnaṃ saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, gihī hīnena khuṃseti hīnena vambheti, gihīnaṃ dhammikaṃ paṭissavaṃ na saccāpeti—**he disparages the Buddha to householders; he disparages the Teaching to householders; he disparages the Sangha to householders; he demeans and insults householders; he doesn’t fulfill legitimate promises to householders.*";
P_HTM[988]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[989]="*Pañcannaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ kareyya.**“The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of reconciliation against five kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[990]="*Eko gihīnaṃ alābhāya parisakkati, eko gihīnaṃ anatthāya parisakkati, eko gihīnaṃ anāvāsāya parisakkati, eko gihī akkosati paribhāsati, eko gihī gihīhi bhedeti—**those who are trying to stop householders from acquiring material gain; those who are trying to harm householders; those who are trying to get householders to lose their place of residence; those who abuse and revile householders; those who cause division between householders.*";
P_HTM[991]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[992]="*Aparesampi, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ kareyya.**The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of reconciliation against another five kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[993]="*Eko gihīnaṃ buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, eko gihīnaṃ dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, eko gihīnaṃ saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, eko gihī hīnena khuṃseti hīnena vambheti, eko gihīnaṃ dhammikaṃ paṭissavaṃ na saccāpeti—**those who disparage the Buddha to householders; those who disparage the Teaching to householders; those who disparage the Sangha to householders; those who demean and insult householders; those who don’t fulfill legitimate promises to householders.”*";
P_HTM[994]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[995]="*Ākaṅkhamānacatukkaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of four on wishing is finished.*";
P_HTM[996]="*4.4. Aṭṭhārasavatta**4.4 The eighteen kinds of conduct*";
P_HTM[997]="*Paṭisāraṇīyakammakatena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā sammā vattitabbaṃ.**“A monk who has had a legal procedure of reconciliation done against himself should conduct himself properly.*";
P_HTM[998]="*Tatrāyaṃ sammāvattanā—**This is the proper conduct:*";
P_HTM[999]="*na upasampādetabbaṃ,**He should not give the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[1000]="*na nissayo dātabbo,**He should not give formal support.*";
P_HTM[1001]="*na sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo,**He should not have a novice monk attend on him.*";
P_HTM[1002]="*na bhikkhunovādakasammuti sāditabbā,**He should not accept being appointed as an instructor of the nuns.*";
P_HTM[1003]="*sammatenapi bhikkhuniyo na ovaditabbā.**Even if appointed, he should not instruct the nuns.*";
P_HTM[1004]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ kataṃ hoti sā āpatti na āpajjitabbā,**He should not commit the same offense as the offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of reconciliation against him.*";
P_HTM[1005]="*aññā vā tādisikā,**He should not commit an offense similar to the offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of reconciliation against him.*";
P_HTM[1006]="*tato vā pāpiṭṭhatarā;**He should not commit an offense worse than the offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of reconciliation against him.*";
P_HTM[1007]="*kammaṃ na garahitabbaṃ,**He should not criticize the procedure.*";
P_HTM[1008]="*kammikā na garahitabbā.**He should not criticize those who did the procedure.*";
P_HTM[1009]="*Na pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposatho ṭhapetabbo,**He should not cancel the observance-day procedure of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[1010]="*na pavāraṇā ṭhapetabbā,**He should not cancel the invitation procedure of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[1011]="*na savacanīyaṃ kātabbaṃ,**He should not speak to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him.*";
P_HTM[1012]="*na anuvādo paṭṭhapetabbo,**He should not make accusations against a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[1013]="*na okāso kāretabbo,**He should not ask a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense.*";
P_HTM[1014]="*na codetabbo,**He should not accuse a regular monk of an offense.*";
P_HTM[1015]="*na sāretabbo,**He should not remind a regular monk of an offense.*";
P_HTM[1016]="*na bhikkhūhi sampayojetabban”ti.**He should not associate inappropriately with other monks.”*";
P_HTM[1017]="*Paṭisāraṇīyakamme aṭṭhārasavattaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The eighteen kinds of conduct in regard to the legal procedure of reconciliation are finished.*";
P_HTM[1018]="*Atha kho saṅgho sudhammassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ akāsi—**Soon afterwards the Sangha did a legal procedure of reconciliation against the monk Sudhamma,*";
P_HTM[1019]="*“citto te gahapati khamāpetabbo”ti.**instructing him to ask Citta for forgiveness.*";
P_HTM[1020]="*So saṅghena paṭisāraṇīyakammakato macchikāsaṇḍaṃ gantvā maṅkubhūto nāsakkhi cittaṃ gahapatiṃ khamāpetuṃ.**He went to Macchikāsaṇḍa, but feeling humiliated, he was unable to ask Citta for forgiveness.*";
P_HTM[1021]="*Punadeva sāvatthiṃ paccāgañchi.**He returned to Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[1022]="*Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—**The monks asked him*";
P_HTM[1023]="*“khamāpito tayā, āvuso sudhamma, citto gahapatī”ti?**if he had asked Citta for forgiveness,*";
P_HTM[1024]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, macchikāsaṇḍaṃ gantvā maṅkubhūto nāsakkhiṃ cittaṃ gahapatiṃ khamāpetun”ti.**and he told them what had happened.*";
P_HTM[1025]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe….**The monks told the Buddha. He had the monks gathered and said,*";
P_HTM[1026]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho sudhammassa bhikkhuno anudūtaṃ detu—**“Well then, the Sangha should give a companion messenger to Sudhamma*";
P_HTM[1027]="*cittaṃ gahapatiṃ khamāpetuṃ.**to ask Citta for forgiveness.*";
P_HTM[1028]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbo—**And this is how the messenger should be given.*";
P_HTM[1029]="*paṭhamaṃ bhikkhu yācitabbo, yācitvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**First you should ask a monk, and then a competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[1030]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1031]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ sudhammassa bhikkhuno anudūtaṃ dadeyya cittaṃ gahapatiṃ khamāpetuṃ.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should give monk so-and-so to Sudhamma as a companion messenger to ask Citta for forgiveness.*";
P_HTM[1032]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[1033]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1034]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ sudhammassa bhikkhuno anudūtaṃ deti cittaṃ gahapatiṃ khamāpetuṃ.**The Sangha gives monk so-and-so to Sudhamma as a companion messenger to ask Citta for forgiveness.*";
P_HTM[1035]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno sudhammassa bhikkhuno anudūtassa dānaṃ cittaṃ gahapatiṃ khamāpetuṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of giving monk so-and-so to Sudhamma as a companion messenger to ask Citta for forgiveness should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[1036]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[1037]="*Dinno saṅghena itthannāmo bhikkhu sudhammassa bhikkhuno anudūto cittaṃ gahapatiṃ khamāpetuṃ.**The Sangha has given monk so-and-so to Sudhamma as a companion messenger to ask Citta for forgiveness.*";
P_HTM[1038]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[1039]="*Tena, bhikkhave, sudhammena bhikkhunā anudūtena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ macchikāsaṇḍaṃ gantvā citto gahapati khamāpetabbo—**“Sudhamma should now go to Macchikāsaṇḍa with that monk as a companion messenger to ask Citta for forgiveness, saying,*";
P_HTM[1040]="*‘khama, gahapati, pasādemi tan’ti.**‘Please forgive me, householder; I wish to reconcile with you.’*";
P_HTM[1041]="*Evañce vuccamāno khamati, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ.**If he forgives, all is well.*";
P_HTM[1042]="*No ce khamati, anudūtena bhikkhunā vattabbo—**If not, the companion messenger should say,*";
P_HTM[1043]="*‘khama, gahapati, imassa bhikkhuno, pasādeti tan’ti.**‘Please forgive this monk, householder; he wishes to reconcile with you.’*";
P_HTM[1044]="*Evañce vuccamāno khamati, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ.**If he forgives, all is well.*";
P_HTM[1045]="*No ce khamati, anudūtena bhikkhunā vattabbo—**If not, the companion messenger should say,*";
P_HTM[1046]="*‘khama, gahapati, imassa bhikkhuno, ahaṃ taṃ pasādemī’ti.**‘Please forgive this monk, householder; I wish to reconcile with you.’*";
P_HTM[1047]="*Evañce vuccamāno khamati, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ.**If he forgives, all is well.*";
P_HTM[1048]="*No ce khamati, anudūtena bhikkhunā vattabbo—**If not, the companion messenger should say,*";
P_HTM[1049]="*‘khama, gahapati, imassa bhikkhuno, saṅghassa vacanenā’ti.**‘Please forgive this monk, householder; I ask in the name of the Sangha.’*";
P_HTM[1050]="*Evañce vuccamāno khamati, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ.**If he forgives, all is well.*";
P_HTM[1051]="*No ce khamati, anudūtena bhikkhunā sudhammo bhikkhu cittassa gahapatino dassanūpacāraṃ avijahāpetvā savanūpacāraṃ avijahāpetvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ kārāpetvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīdāpetvā añjaliṃ paggaṇhāpetvā taṃ āpattiṃ desāpetabbo”ti.**If not, then within sight and hearing of Citta, the monk Sudhamma should put his upper robe over one shoulder, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and confess that offense.”*";
P_HTM[1052]="*Atha kho āyasmā sudhammo anudūtena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ macchikāsaṇḍaṃ gantvā cittaṃ gahapatiṃ khamāpesi.**Soon afterwards Sudhamma went to Macchikāsaṇḍa with a monk as a companion messenger, and he asked Citta for forgiveness.*";
P_HTM[1053]="*So sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, bhikkhū upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeti—**And he conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released. He then went to the monks*";
P_HTM[1054]="*“ahaṃ, āvuso, saṅghena paṭisāraṇīyakammakato sammā vattāmi, lomaṃ pātemi, netthāraṃ vattāmi.**and told them about this,*";
P_HTM[1055]="*Kathaṃ nu kho mayā paṭipajjitabban”ti?**adding, “What should I do now?”*";
P_HTM[1056]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**The monks told the Buddha. He had the monks gathered and said,*";
P_HTM[1057]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho sudhammassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetu.**“Well then, lift that legal procedure of reconciliation against Sudhamma.*";
P_HTM[1058]="*4.5. Nappaṭippassambhetabbaaṭṭhārasaka**4.5 The group of eighteen on not to be lifted*";
P_HTM[1059]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**“When a monk has five qualities, a legal procedure of reconciliation against him should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1060]="*Upasampādeti, nissayaṃ deti, sāmaṇeraṃ upaṭṭhāpeti, bhikkhunovādakasammutiṃ sādiyati, sammatopi bhikkhuniyo ovadati—**he gives the full ordination; he gives formal support; he has a novice monk attend on him; he accepts being appointed as an instructor of the nuns; he instructs the nuns, whether appointed or not.*";
P_HTM[1061]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1062]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of reconciliation against him should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1063]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ kataṃ hoti taṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati, aññaṃ vā tādisikaṃ, tato vā pāpiṭṭhataraṃ;**he commits the same offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of reconciliation against him; he commits an offense similar to the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of reconciliation against him; he commits an offense worse than the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of reconciliation against him;*";
P_HTM[1064]="*kammaṃ garahati, kammike garahati—**he criticizes the procedure; he criticizes those who did the procedure.*";
P_HTM[1065]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1066]="*Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has eight qualities, a procedure of reconciliation against him should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1067]="*Pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposathaṃ ṭhapeti, pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapeti, savacanīyaṃ karoti, anuvādaṃ paṭṭhapeti, okāsaṃ kāreti, codeti, sāreti, bhikkhūhi sampayojeti—**he cancels the observance-day procedure of a regular monk; he cancels the invitation procedure of a regular monk; he speaks to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him; he makes accusations against a regular monk; he asks a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense; he accuses a regular monk of an offense; he reminds a regular monk of an offense; he associates inappropriately with other monks.”*";
P_HTM[1068]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1069]="*Paṭisāraṇīyakamme nappaṭippassambhetabbaaṭṭhārasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of eighteen on not to be lifted is finished.*";
P_HTM[1070]="*4.6. Paṭippassambhetabbaaṭṭhārasaka**4.6 The group of eighteen on to be lifted*";
P_HTM[1071]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**“When a monk has five qualities, a legal procedure of reconciliation against him should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1072]="*Na upasampādeti, na nissayaṃ deti, na sāmaṇeraṃ upaṭṭhāpeti, na bhikkhunovādakasammutiṃ sādiyati, sammatopi bhikkhuniyo na ovadati—**he does not give the full ordination; he does not give formal support; he does not have a novice monk attend on him; he does not accept being appointed as an instructor of the nuns; he does not instruct the nuns, whether appointed or not.*";
P_HTM[1073]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1074]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of reconciliation against him should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1075]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ kataṃ hoti taṃ āpattiṃ na āpajjati, aññaṃ vā tādisikaṃ, tato vā pāpiṭṭhataraṃ;**he doesn’t commit the same offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of reconciliation against him; he doesn’t commit an offense similar to the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of reconciliation against him; he doesn’t commit an offense worse than the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of reconciliation against him;*";
P_HTM[1076]="*kammaṃ na garahati, kammike na garahati—**he doesn’t criticize the procedure; he doesn’t criticize those who did the procedure.*";
P_HTM[1077]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1078]="*Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has eight qualities, a procedure of reconciliation against him should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1079]="*Na pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposathaṃ ṭhapeti, na pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapeti, na savacanīyaṃ karoti, na anuvādaṃ paṭṭhapeti, na okāsaṃ kāreti, na codeti, na sāreti, na bhikkhūhi sampayojeti—**he doesn’t cancel the observance-day procedure of a regular monk; he doesn’t cancel the invitation procedure of a regular monk; he doesn’t speak to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him; he doesn’t make accusations against a regular monk; he doesn’t ask a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense; he doesn’t accuse a regular monk of an offense; he doesn’t remind a regular monk of an offense; he doesn’t associate inappropriately with other monks.”*";
P_HTM[1080]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1081]="*Paṭisāraṇīyakamme paṭippassambhetabbaaṭṭhārasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of eighteen on to be lifted is finished.*";
P_HTM[1082]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**“And this is how it should be lifted.*";
P_HTM[1083]="*Tena, bhikkhave, sudhammena bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**The monk Sudhamma should approach the Sangha, put his upper robes over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[1084]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, saṅghena paṭisāraṇīyakammakato sammā vattāmi, lomaṃ pātemi, netthāraṃ vattāmi, paṭisāraṇīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācāmī’ti.**‘Venerables, the Sangha has done a legal procedure of reconciliation against me, but I have conducted myself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released. I ask for the legal procedure of reconciliation to be lifted.’*";
P_HTM[1085]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbā.**And he should ask a second*";
P_HTM[1086]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[1087]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[1088]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1089]="*Ayaṃ sudhammo bhikkhu saṅghena paṭisāraṇīyakammakato sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, paṭisāraṇīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācati.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of reconciliation against the monk Sudhamma. He has conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now asks for the legal procedure of reconciliation to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[1090]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho sudhammassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ paṭippassambheyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should lift the legal procedure of reconciliation against him.*";
P_HTM[1091]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[1092]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1093]="*Ayaṃ sudhammo bhikkhu saṅghena paṭisāraṇīyakammakato sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, paṭisāraṇīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācati.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of reconciliation against the monk Sudhamma. He has conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now asks for the legal procedure of reconciliation to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[1094]="*Saṅgho sudhammassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ paṭippassambheti.**The Sangha lifts the legal procedure of reconciliation against him.*";
P_HTM[1095]="*Yassāyasmato khamati sudhammassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhi, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of lifting the legal procedure of reconciliation against the monk Sudhamma should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[1096]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[1097]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[1098]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—**For the third time I speak on this matter.*";
P_HTM[1099]="*suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1100]="*Ayaṃ sudhammo bhikkhu saṅghena paṭisāraṇīyakammakato sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, paṭisāraṇīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācati.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of reconciliation against the monk Sudhamma. He has conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now asks for the legal procedure of reconciliation to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[1101]="*Saṅgho sudhammassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ paṭippassambheti.**The Sangha lifts the legal procedure of reconciliation against him.*";
P_HTM[1102]="*Yassāyasmato khamati sudhammassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhi, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of lifting the legal procedure of reconciliation against the monk Sudhamma should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[1103]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[1104]="*Paṭippassaddhaṃ saṅghena sudhammassa bhikkhuno paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ.**The Sangha has lifted the legal procedure of reconciliation against the monk Sudhamma.*";
P_HTM[1105]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[1106]="*Paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ.**The fourth section on the legal procedure of reconciliation is finished.*";
P_HTM[1107]="*5. Āpattiyāadassaneukkhepanīyakamma**5. The legal procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense*";
P_HTM[1108]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Kosambī in Ghosita’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[1109]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā channo āpattiṃ āpajjitvā na icchati āpattiṃ passituṃ.**At that time Venerable Channa had committed an offense, but refused to recognize it.*";
P_HTM[1110]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[1111]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā channo āpattiṃ āpajjitvā na icchissati āpattiṃ passitun”ti.**“How can Venerable Channa commit an offense, but then refuse to recognize it?”*";
P_HTM[1112]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[1113]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[1114]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, channo bhikkhu āpattiṃ āpajjitvā na icchati āpattiṃ passitun”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that Channa is acting like this?”*";
P_HTM[1115]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[1116]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—**The Buddha criticized him,*";
P_HTM[1117]="*“ananucchavikaṃ …pe…**“It’s not suitable …*";
P_HTM[1118]="*kathañhi nāma so, bhikkhave, moghapuriso āpattiṃ āpajjitvā na icchissati āpattiṃ passituṃ?**How can Channa commit an offense, but then refuse to recognize it?*";
P_HTM[1119]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[1120]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**and after criticizing him …*";
P_HTM[1121]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[1122]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ karotu—**“Well then, the Sangha should do a legal procedure of ejecting the monk Channa for not recognizing an offense,*";
P_HTM[1123]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena.**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1124]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, kātabbaṃ—**And this is how it should be done.*";
P_HTM[1125]="*paṭhamaṃ channo bhikkhu codetabbo, codetvā sāretabbo, sāretvā āpattiṃ āropetabbo, āpattiṃ āropetvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**First you should accuse the monk Channa. He should then be reminded of what he has done, before he is charged with an offense. A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[1126]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1127]="*Ayaṃ channo bhikkhu āpattiṃ āpajjitvā na icchati āpattiṃ passituṃ.**The monk Channa has committed an offense, but refuses to recognize it.*";
P_HTM[1128]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya—**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should do a legal procedure of ejecting Channa for not recognizing an offense,*";
P_HTM[1129]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena.**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1130]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[1131]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1132]="*Ayaṃ channo bhikkhu āpattiṃ āpajjitvā na icchati āpattiṃ passituṃ.**The monk Channa has committed an offense, but refuses to recognize it.*";
P_HTM[1133]="*Saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ karoti—**The Sangha is doing a legal procedure of ejecting Channa for not recognizing an offense,*";
P_HTM[1134]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena.**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1135]="*Yassāyasmato khamati channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyassa kammassa karaṇaṃ—**Any monk who approves of doing a legal procedure of ejecting Channa for not recognizing an offense,*";
P_HTM[1136]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena, so tuṇhassa;**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha, should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[1137]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[1138]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter …*";
P_HTM[1139]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—**For the third time I speak on this matter.*";
P_HTM[1140]="*suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1141]="*Ayaṃ channo bhikkhu āpattiṃ āpajjitvā na icchati āpattiṃ passituṃ.**The monk Channa has committed an offense, but refuses to recognize it.*";
P_HTM[1142]="*Saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ karoti—**The Sangha is doing a legal procedure of ejecting Channa for not recognizing an offense,*";
P_HTM[1143]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena.**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1144]="*Yassāyasmato khamati channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyassa kammassa karaṇaṃ—**Any monk who approves of doing a legal procedure of ejecting Channa for not recognizing an offense,*";
P_HTM[1145]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena, so tuṇhassa;**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha, should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[1146]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[1147]="*Kataṃ saṅghena channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ—**The Sangha has done the legal procedure of ejecting Channa for not recognizing an offense,*";
P_HTM[1148]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena.**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1149]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[1150]="*Āvāsaparamparañca, bhikkhave, saṃsatha—**Monks, you should proclaim from monastery to monastery*";
P_HTM[1151]="*‘channo bhikkhu saṅghena āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammakato—**that the Sangha has done a legal procedure of ejecting Channa for not recognizing an offense,*";
P_HTM[1152]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghenā’ti.**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1153]="*5.1. Adhammakammadvādasaka**5.1 The group of twelve on illegitimate legal procedures*";
P_HTM[1154]="*Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgataṃ, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.**“When a legal procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has three qualities, it is illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[1155]="*Asammukhā kataṃ hoti, appaṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, appaṭiññāya kataṃ hoti—**it is done in the absence of the accused, it is done without questioning the accused, it is done without the admission of the accused.*";
P_HTM[1156]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[1157]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.**When a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[1158]="*Anāpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adesanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, desitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti …pe…**it is done against one who hasn’t committed any offense, it is done against one who has committed an offense that isn’t clearable by confession, it is done against one who has confessed their offense.*";
P_HTM[1159]="*acodetvā kataṃ hoti, asāretvā kataṃ hoti, āpattiṃ anāropetvā kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having accused the person of their offense, it is done without having reminded the person of their offense, it is done without having charged the person with their offense.*";
P_HTM[1160]="*asammukhā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done in the absence of the accused, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1161]="*appaṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without questioning the accused, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1162]="*appaṭiññāya kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without the admission of the accused, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1163]="*anāpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done against one who hasn’t committed any offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1164]="*adesanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done against one who has committed an offense that isn’t clearable by confession, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1165]="*desitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done against one who has confessed their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1166]="*acodetvā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having accused the person of their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1167]="*asāretvā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having reminded the person of their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1168]="*āpattiṃ anāropetvā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti—**When a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having charged the person with their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.”*";
P_HTM[1169]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[1170]="*Āpattiyā adassane ukkhepanīyakamme adhammakammadvādasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of twelve on illegitimate legal procedures of ejection for not recognizing an offense is finished.*";
P_HTM[1171]="*5.2. Dhammakammadvādasaka**5.2 The group of twelve on legitimate legal procedures*";
P_HTM[1172]="*Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgataṃ, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.**“When a legal procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has three qualities, it is legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[1173]="*Sammukhā kataṃ hoti, paṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, paṭiññāya kataṃ hoti—**it is done in the presence of the accused, it is done with the questioning of the accused, it is done with the admission of the accused.*";
P_HTM[1174]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[1175]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ …pe….**When a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[1176]="*Āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, desanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adesitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti …pe…**it is done against one who has committed an offense, it is done against one who has committed an offense that is clearable by confession, it is done against one who hasn’t confessed their offense.*";
P_HTM[1177]="*codetvā kataṃ hoti, sāretvā kataṃ hoti, āpattiṃ āropetvā kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done after having accused the person of their offense, it is done after having reminded the person of their offense, it is done after having charged the person with their offense.*";
P_HTM[1178]="*sammukhā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done in the presence of the accused, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1179]="*paṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done with the questioning of the accused, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1180]="*paṭiññāya kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done with the admission of the accused, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1181]="*āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done against one who has committed an offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1182]="*desanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done against one who has committed an offense that is clearable by confession, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1183]="*adesitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done against one who hasn’t confessed their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1184]="*codetvā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done after having accused the person of their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1185]="*sāretvā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done after having reminded the person of their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1186]="*āpattiṃ āropetvā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti—**When a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done after having charged the person with their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.”*";
P_HTM[1187]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[1188]="*Āpattiyā adassane ukkhepanīyakamme dhammakammadvādasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of twelve on legitimate legal procedures of ejection for not recognizing an offense is finished.*";
P_HTM[1189]="*5.3. Ākaṅkhamānachakka**5.3 The group of six on wishing*";
P_HTM[1190]="*Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**“When a monk has three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a legal procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense:*";
P_HTM[1191]="*Bhaṇḍanakārako hoti kalahakārako vivādakārako bhassakārako saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako;**he is quarrelsome, argumentative, and a creator of legal issues in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[1192]="*bālo hoti abyatto āpattibahulo anapadāno;**he is ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, incapable of determining whether he has committed an offense;*";
P_HTM[1193]="*gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi—**he is constantly and improperly socializing with householders.*";
P_HTM[1194]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[1195]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**When a monk has another three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense:*";
P_HTM[1196]="*Adhisīle sīlavipanno hoti, ajjhācāre ācāravipanno hoti, atidiṭṭhiyā diṭṭhivipanno hoti—**he has failed in the higher morality; he has failed in conduct; he has failed in view.*";
P_HTM[1197]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[1198]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**When a monk has another three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense:*";
P_HTM[1199]="*Buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—**he disparages the Buddha; he disparages the Teaching; he disparages the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1200]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[1201]="*Tiṇṇaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**“The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense against three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[1202]="*Eko bhaṇḍanakārako hoti kalahakārako vivādakārako bhassakārako saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako;**those who are quarrelsome, argumentative, and creators of legal issues in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[1203]="*eko bālo hoti abyatto āpattibahulo anapadāno;**those who are ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, incapable of determining whether they have committed an offense;*";
P_HTM[1204]="*eko gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi—**those who are constantly and improperly socializing with householders.*";
P_HTM[1205]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[1206]="*Aparesampi, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense against another three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[1207]="*Eko adhisīle sīlavipanno hoti, eko ajjhācāre ācāravipanno hoti, eko atidiṭṭhiyā diṭṭhivipanno hoti—**those who have failed in the higher morality; those who have failed in conduct; those who have failed in view.*";
P_HTM[1208]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[1209]="*Aparesampi, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense against another three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[1210]="*Eko buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, eko dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, eko saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—**those who disparage the Buddha; those who disparage the Teaching; those who disparage the Sangha.”*";
P_HTM[1211]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[1212]="*Āpattiyā adassane ukkhepanīyakamme ākaṅkhamānachakkaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of six on wishing in regard to a procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense is finished.*";
P_HTM[1213]="*5.4. Tecattālīsavatta**5.4 The forty-three kinds of conduct*";
P_HTM[1214]="*Āpattiyā adassane ukkhepanīyakammakatena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā sammā vattitabbaṃ.**“A monk who has had a legal procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense done against himself should conduct himself properly.*";
P_HTM[1215]="*Tatrāyaṃ sammāvattanā—**This is the proper conduct:*";
P_HTM[1216]="*na upasampādetabbaṃ,**He should not give the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[1217]="*na nissayo dātabbo,**He should not give formal support.*";
P_HTM[1218]="*na sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo,**He should not have a novice monk attend on him.*";
P_HTM[1219]="*na bhikkhunovādakasammuti sāditabbā,**He should not accept being appointed as an instructor of the nuns.*";
P_HTM[1220]="*sammatenapi bhikkhuniyo na ovaditabbā.**Even if appointed, he should not instruct the nuns.*";
P_HTM[1221]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena āpattiyā adassane ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kataṃ hoti sā āpatti na āpajjitabbā,**He should not commit the same offense as the offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense.*";
P_HTM[1222]="*aññā vā tādisikā,**He should not commit an offense similar to the offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense.*";
P_HTM[1223]="*tato vā pāpiṭṭhatarā;**He should not commit an offense worse than the offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense.*";
P_HTM[1224]="*kammaṃ na garahitabbaṃ,**He should not criticize the procedure.*";
P_HTM[1225]="*kammikā na garahitabbā.**He should not criticize those who did the procedure.*";
P_HTM[1226]="*Na pakatattassa bhikkhuno abhivādanaṃ,**He should not consent to a regular monk bowing down to him.*";
P_HTM[1227]="*paccuṭṭhānaṃ,**He should not consent to a regular monk standing up for him.*";
P_HTM[1228]="*añjalikammaṃ,**He should not consent to a regular monk raise his joined palms to him.*";
P_HTM[1229]="*sāmīcikammaṃ,**He should not consent to a regular monk doing acts of respect toward him.*";
P_HTM[1230]="*āsanābhihāro,**He should not consent to a regular monk offering him a seat.*";
P_HTM[1231]="*seyyābhihāro,**He should not consent to a regular monk offering him a bed.*";
P_HTM[1232]="*pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ,**He should not consent to a regular monk offering him water for washing his feet and a foot stool.*";
P_HTM[1233]="*pādakathalikaṃ,**He should not consent to a regular monk offering him a foot scraper.*";
P_HTM[1234]="*pattacīvarappaṭiggahaṇaṃ,**He should not consent to a regular monk receiving his bowl and robe.*";
P_HTM[1235]="*nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ sāditabbaṃ.**He should not consent to a regular monk massaging his back when bathing.*";
P_HTM[1236]="*Na pakatatto bhikkhu sīlavipattiyā anuddhaṃsetabbo,**He should not charge a regular monk with failure in morality.*";
P_HTM[1237]="*na ācāravipattiyā anuddhaṃsetabbo,**He should not charge a regular monk with failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[1238]="*na diṭṭhivipattiyā anuddhaṃsetabbo,**He should not charge a regular monk with failure in view.*";
P_HTM[1239]="*na ājīvavipattiyā anuddhaṃsetabbo,**He should not charge a regular monk with failure in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[1240]="*na bhikkhu bhikkhūhi bhedetabbo,**He should not cause division between monks.*";
P_HTM[1241]="*na gihiddhajo dhāretabbo,**He should not wear lay clothes.*";
P_HTM[1242]="*na titthiyaddhajo dhāretabbo,**He should not wear the robes of the monastics of other religions.*";
P_HTM[1243]="*na titthiyā sevitabbā;**He should not associate with the monastics of other religions.*";
P_HTM[1244]="*bhikkhū sevitabbā,**He should associate with monks.*";
P_HTM[1245]="*bhikkhusikkhāya sikkhitabbaṃ.**He should train in the monks’ training.*";
P_HTM[1246]="*Na pakatattena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ ekacchanne āvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not stay in the same room in a monastery as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[1247]="*na ekacchanne anāvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not stay in the same room in a non-monastery as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[1248]="*na ekacchanne āvāse vā anāvāse vā vatthabbaṃ,**He should not stay in the same room in a monastery or a non-monastery as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[1249]="*pakatattaṃ bhikkhuṃ disvā āsanā vuṭṭhātabbaṃ,**He should get up from his seat when he sees a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[1250]="*na pakatatto bhikkhu āsādetabbo anto vā bahi vā.**He should not dismiss a regular monk, whether inside or outside a dwelling.*";
P_HTM[1251]="*Na pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposatho ṭhapetabbo,**He should not cancel the observance-day procedure of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[1252]="*na pavāraṇā ṭhapetabbā,**He should not cancel the invitation procedure of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[1253]="*na savacanīyaṃ kātabbaṃ,**He should not speak to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him.*";
P_HTM[1254]="*na anuvādo paṭṭhapetabbo,**He should not make accusations against a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[1255]="*na okāso kāretabbo,**He should not ask a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense.*";
P_HTM[1256]="*na codetabbo,**He should not accuse a regular monk of an offense.*";
P_HTM[1257]="*na sāretabbo,**He should not remind a regular monk of an offense.*";
P_HTM[1258]="*na bhikkhūhi sampayojetabban”ti.**He should not associate inappropriately with other monks.”*";
P_HTM[1259]="*Āpattiyā adassane ukkhepanīyakamme tecattālīsavattaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The forty-three kinds of conduct in regard to the legal procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense are finished.*";
P_HTM[1260]="*Atha kho saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ akāsi—**Soon afterwards the Sangha did a legal procedure of ejecting the monk Channa for not recognizing an offense,*";
P_HTM[1261]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena.**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1262]="*So saṅghena, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammakato tamhā āvāsā aññaṃ āvāsaṃ agamāsi.**He then left that monastery and went to another one.*";
P_HTM[1263]="*Tattha bhikkhū neva abhivādesuṃ, na paccuṭṭhesuṃ, na añjalikammaṃ na sāmīcikammaṃ akaṃsu, na sakkariṃsu, na garuṃ kariṃsu, na mānesuṃ, na pūjesuṃ.**The monks there did not bow down to him, stand up for him, raise their joined palms to him, or do acts of respect toward him. They did not honor, respect, or esteem him.*";
P_HTM[1264]="*So bhikkhūhi asakkariyamāno agarukariyamāno amāniyamāno apūjiyamāno asakkārapakato tamhāpi āvāsā aññaṃ āvāsaṃ agamāsi.**Because of this, he left that monastery too and went to yet another one.*";
P_HTM[1265]="*Tatthapi bhikkhū neva abhivādesuṃ, na paccuṭṭhesuṃ, na añjalikammaṃ na sāmīcikammaṃ akaṃsu, na sakkariṃsu, na garuṃ kariṃsu, na mānesuṃ, na pūjesuṃ.**There too the monks did not bow down to him, stand up for him, raise their joined palms to him, or do acts of respect toward him. They did not honor, respect, or esteem him.*";
P_HTM[1266]="*So bhikkhūhi asakkariyamāno agarukariyamāno amāniyamāno apūjiyamāno asakkārapakato tamhāpi āvāsā aññaṃ āvāsaṃ agamāsi.**Because of this, he left that monastery too and went to yet another one.*";
P_HTM[1267]="*Tatthapi bhikkhū neva abhivādesuṃ, na paccuṭṭhesuṃ, na añjalikammaṃ na sāmīcikammaṃ akaṃsu, na sakkariṃsu, na garuṃ kariṃsu, na mānesuṃ, na pūjesuṃ.**There too the monks did not bow down to him, stand up for him, raise their joined palms to him, or do acts of respect toward him. They did not honor, respect, or esteem him.*";
P_HTM[1268]="*So bhikkhūhi asakkariyamāno agarukariyamāno amāniyamāno apūjiyamāno asakkārapakato punadeva kosambiṃ paccāgañchi.**Because of this, he left that monastery too and returned to Kosambī.*";
P_HTM[1269]="*So sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, bhikkhū upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeti—**He then conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released. He went to the monks*";
P_HTM[1270]="*“ahaṃ, āvuso, saṅghena, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammakato sammā vattāmi, lomaṃ pātemi, netthāraṃ vattāmi.**and told them about this,*";
P_HTM[1271]="*Kathaṃ nu kho mayā paṭipajjitabban”ti?**adding, “What should I do now?”*";
P_HTM[1272]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe….**The monks told the Buddha. He had the monks gathered and said,*";
P_HTM[1273]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetu.**“Well then, lift that legal procedure of ejecting the monk Channa for not recognizing an offense.*";
P_HTM[1274]="*5.5. Nappaṭippassambhetabbatecattālīsaka**5.5 The group of forty-three on not to be lifted*";
P_HTM[1275]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**“When a monk has five qualities, a legal procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1276]="*Upasampādeti, nissayaṃ deti, sāmaṇeraṃ upaṭṭhāpeti, bhikkhunovādakasammutiṃ sādiyati, sammatopi bhikkhuniyo ovadati—**he gives the full ordination; he gives formal support; he has a novice monk attend on him; he accepts being appointed as an instructor of the nuns; he instructs the nuns, whether appointed or not.*";
P_HTM[1277]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1278]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1279]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kataṃ hoti taṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati, aññaṃ vā tādisikaṃ, tato vā pāpiṭṭhataraṃ;**he commits the same offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense; he commits an offense similar to the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense; he commits an offense worse than the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense;*";
P_HTM[1280]="*kammaṃ garahati, kammike garahati—**he criticizes the procedure; he criticizes those who did the procedure.*";
P_HTM[1281]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1282]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1283]="*Pakatattassa bhikkhuno abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ, añjalikammaṃ, sāmīcikammaṃ, āsanābhihāraṃ sādiyati—**he consents to a regular monk bowing down to him; he consents to a regular monk standing up for him; he consents to a regular monk raising his joined palms to him; he consents to a regular monk doing acts of respect toward him; he consents to a regular monk offering him a seat.*";
P_HTM[1284]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1285]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1286]="*Pakatattassa bhikkhuno seyyābhihāraṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ, pādakathalikaṃ, pattacīvarappaṭiggahaṇaṃ, nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ sādiyati—**he consents to a regular monk offering him a bed; he consents to a regular monk offering him water for washing his feet and a foot stool; he consents to a regular monk offering him a foot scraper; he consents to a regular monk receiving his bowl and robe; he consents to a regular monk massaging his back when bathing.*";
P_HTM[1287]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1288]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1289]="*Pakatattaṃ bhikkhuṃ sīlavipattiyā anuddhaṃseti, ācāravipattiyā anuddhaṃseti, diṭṭhivipattiyā anuddhaṃseti, ājīvavipattiyā anuddhaṃseti, bhikkhuṃ bhikkhūhi bhedeti—**he charges a regular monk with failure in morality; he charges a regular monk with failure in conduct; he charges a regular monk with failure in view; he charges a regular monk with failure in livelihood; he causes division between monks.*";
P_HTM[1290]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1291]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1292]="*Gihiddhajaṃ dhāreti, titthiyaddhajaṃ dhāreti, titthiye sevati;**he wears lay clothes; he wears the robes of the monastics of other religions; he associates with the monastics of other religions;*";
P_HTM[1293]="*bhikkhū na sevati, bhikkhusikkhāya na sikkhati—**he doesn’t associate with monks; he doesn’t train in the monks’ training.*";
P_HTM[1294]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1295]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1296]="*Pakatattena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ ekacchanne āvāse vasati, ekacchanne anāvāse vasati, ekacchanne āvāse vā anāvāse vā vasati;**he stays in the same room in a monastery as a regular monk; he stays in the same room in a non-monastery as a regular monk; he stays in the same room in a monastery or a non-monastery as a regular monk;*";
P_HTM[1297]="*pakatattaṃ bhikkhuṃ disvā āsanā na vuṭṭhāti;**he doesn’t get up from his seat when he sees a regular monk;*";
P_HTM[1298]="*pakatattaṃ bhikkhuṃ āsādeti anto vā bahi vā—**he dismisses a regular monk, whether inside or outside a dwelling.*";
P_HTM[1299]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1300]="*Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has eight qualities, a procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1301]="*Pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposathaṃ ṭhapeti, pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapeti, savacanīyaṃ karoti, anuvādaṃ paṭṭhapeti, okāsaṃ kāreti, codeti, sāreti, bhikkhūhi sampayojeti—**he cancels the observance-day procedure of a regular monk; he cancels the invitation procedure of a regular monk; he speaks to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him; he makes accusations against a regular monk; he asks a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense; he accuses a regular monk of an offense; he reminds a regular monk of an offense; he associates inappropriately with other monks.”*";
P_HTM[1302]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1303]="*Āpattiyā adassane ukkhepanīyakamme nappaṭippassambhetabbatecattālīsakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of forty-three on not to be lifted in regard to the legal procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense is finished.*";
P_HTM[1304]="*5.6. Paṭippassambhetabbatecattālīsaka**5.6 The group of forty-three on to be lifted*";
P_HTM[1305]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**“When a monk has five qualities, a legal procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1306]="*Na upasampādeti, na nissayaṃ deti, na sāmaṇeraṃ upaṭṭhāpeti, na bhikkhunovādakasammutiṃ sādiyati, sammatopi bhikkhuniyo na ovadati—**he does not give the full ordination; he does not give formal support; he does not have a novice monk attend on him; he does not accept being appointed as an instructor of the nuns; he does not instruct the nuns, whether appointed or not.*";
P_HTM[1307]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1308]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1309]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena āpattiyā adassane ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kataṃ hoti taṃ āpattiṃ na āpajjati, aññaṃ vā tādisikaṃ, tato vā pāpiṭṭhataraṃ;**he doesn’t commit the same offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense; he doesn’t commit an offense similar to the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense; he doesn’t commit an offense worse than the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense;*";
P_HTM[1310]="*kammaṃ na garahati, kammike na garahati—**he doesn’t criticize the procedure; he doesn’t criticize those who did the procedure.*";
P_HTM[1311]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1312]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1313]="*Na pakatattassa bhikkhuno abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ, añjalikammaṃ, sāmīcikammaṃ, āsanābhihāraṃ sādiyati—**he doesn’t consent to a regular monk bowing down to him; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk standing up for him; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk raising his joined palms to him; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk doing acts of respect toward him; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk offering him a seat.*";
P_HTM[1314]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1315]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1316]="*Na pakatattassa bhikkhuno seyyābhihāraṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ, pādakathalikaṃ, pattacīvarappaṭiggahaṇaṃ, nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ sādiyati—**he doesn’t consent to a regular monk offering him a bed; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk offering him water for washing his feet and a foot stool; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk offering him a foot scraper; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk receiving his bowl and robe; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk massaging his back when bathing.*";
P_HTM[1317]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1318]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1319]="*Na pakatattaṃ bhikkhuṃ sīlavipattiyā anuddhaṃseti, na ācāravipattiyā anuddhaṃseti, na diṭṭhivipattiyā anuddhaṃseti, na ājīvavipattiyā anuddhaṃseti, na bhikkhuṃ bhikkhūhi bhedeti—**he doesn’t charge a regular monk with failure in morality; he doesn’t charge a regular monk with failure in conduct; he doesn’t charge a regular monk with failure in view; he doesn’t charge a regular monk with failure in livelihood; he doesn’t cause division between monks.*";
P_HTM[1320]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1321]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1322]="*Na gihiddhajaṃ dhāreti, na titthiyaddhajaṃ dhāreti, na titthiye sevati, bhikkhū sevati, bhikkhusikkhāya sikkhati—**he doesn’t wear lay clothes; he doesn’t wear the robes of the monastics of other religions; he doesn’t associate with the monastics of other religions; he associates with monks; he trains in the monks’ training.*";
P_HTM[1323]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1324]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1325]="*Na pakatattena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ ekacchanne āvāse vasati, na ekacchanne anāvāse vasati, na ekacchanne āvāse vā anāvāse vā vasati, pakatattaṃ bhikkhuṃ disvā āsanā vuṭṭhāti, na pakatattaṃ bhikkhuṃ āsādeti anto vā bahi vā—**he doesn’t stay in the same room in a monastery as a regular monk; he doesn’t stay in the same room in a non-monastery as a regular monk; he doesn’t stay in the same room in a monastery or a non-monastery as a regular monk; he gets up from his seat when he sees a regular monk; he doesn’t dismiss a regular monk, whether inside or outside a dwelling.*";
P_HTM[1326]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1327]="*Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has eight qualities, a procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1328]="*Na pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposathaṃ ṭhapeti, na pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapeti, na savacanīyaṃ karoti, na anuvādaṃ paṭṭhapeti, na okāsaṃ kāreti, na codeti, na sāreti, na bhikkhūhi sampayojeti—**he doesn’t cancel the observance-day procedure of a regular monk; he doesn’t cancel the invitation procedure of a regular monk; he doesn’t speak to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him; he doesn’t make accusations against a regular monk; he doesn’t ask a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense; he doesn’t accuse a regular monk of an offense; he doesn’t remind a regular monk of an offense; he doesn’t associate inappropriately with other monks.”*";
P_HTM[1329]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1330]="*Āpattiyā adassane ukkhepanīyakamme paṭippassambhetabbatecattālīsakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of forty-three on to be lifted in regard to the legal procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense is finished.*";
P_HTM[1331]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**“And this is how it should be lifted.*";
P_HTM[1332]="*Tena, bhikkhave, channena bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**The monk Channa should approach the Sangha, put his upper robes over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[1333]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, saṅghena, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammakato sammā vattāmi, lomaṃ pātemi, netthāraṃ vattāmi, āpattiyā adassane ukkhepanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācāmī’ti.**‘Venerables, the Sangha has done a legal procedure of ejecting me for not recognizing an offense, but I have conducted myself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released. I ask for the legal procedure of ejection to be lifted.’*";
P_HTM[1334]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbā.**And he should ask a second*";
P_HTM[1335]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[1336]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[1337]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1338]="*Ayaṃ channo bhikkhu saṅghena, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammakato sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, āpattiyā adassane ukkhepanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācati.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of ejecting the monk Channa for not recognizing an offense. He has conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now asks for the legal procedure of ejection to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[1339]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambheyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should lift the legal procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense.*";
P_HTM[1340]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[1341]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1342]="*Ayaṃ channo bhikkhu saṅghena, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammakato sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācati.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of ejecting the monk Channa for not recognizing an offense. He has conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now asks for the legal procedure of ejection to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[1343]="*Saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambheti.**The Sangha lifts the legal procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense.*";
P_HTM[1344]="*Yassāyasmato khamati channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhi, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of lifting the legal procedure of ejecting the monk Channa for not recognizing an offense should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[1345]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[1346]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[1347]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—**For the third time I speak on this matter.*";
P_HTM[1348]="*suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1349]="*Ayaṃ channo bhikkhu saṅghena, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammakato sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācati.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of ejecting the monk Channa for not recognizing an offense. He has conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now asks for the legal procedure of ejection to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[1350]="*Saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambheti.**The Sangha lifts the legal procedure of ejecting him for not recognizing an offense.*";
P_HTM[1351]="*Yassāyasmato khamati channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhi, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of lifting the legal procedure of ejecting the monk Channa for not recognizing an offense should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[1352]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[1353]="*Paṭippassaddhaṃ saṅghena channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā adassane, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ.**The Sangha has lifted the legal procedure of ejecting the monk Channa for not recognizing an offense.*";
P_HTM[1354]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[1355]="*Āpattiyā adassane ukkhepanīyakammaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ.**The fifth section on the legal procedure of ejection for not recognizing an offense is finished.*";
P_HTM[1356]="*6. Āpattiyāappaṭikammeukkhepanīyakamma**6. The legal procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense*";
P_HTM[1357]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Kosambī in Ghosita’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[1358]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā channo āpattiṃ āpajjitvā na icchati āpattiṃ paṭikātuṃ.**At this time Venerable Channa had committed an offense, but refused to make amends for it.*";
P_HTM[1359]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[1360]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā channo āpattiṃ āpajjitvā na icchissati āpattiṃ paṭikātun”ti?**“How can Venerable Channa commit an offense, but then refuse to make amends for it?”*";
P_HTM[1361]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[1362]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[1363]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, channo bhikkhu āpattiṃ āpajjitvā na icchati āpattiṃ paṭikātun”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that Channa is acting like this?”*";
P_HTM[1364]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[1365]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—**The Buddha criticized him,*";
P_HTM[1366]="*“ananucchavikaṃ …pe…**“It’s not suitable …*";
P_HTM[1367]="*kathañhi nāma so, bhikkhave, moghapuriso āpattiṃ āpajjitvā na icchissati āpattiṃ paṭikātuṃ.**How can Channa commit an offense, but then refuse to make amends for it?*";
P_HTM[1368]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[1369]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**and after criticizing him …*";
P_HTM[1370]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[1371]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ karotu—**“Well then, the Sangha should do a legal procedure of ejecting the monk Channa for not making amends for an offense,*";
P_HTM[1372]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena.**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1373]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, kātabbaṃ—**And this is how it should be done.*";
P_HTM[1374]="*paṭhamaṃ channo bhikkhu codetabbo, codetvā sāretabbo, sāretvā āpattiṃ āropetabbo, āpattiṃ āropetvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**First you should accuse the monk Channa. He should then be reminded of what he has done, before he is charged with an offense. A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[1375]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1376]="*Ayaṃ channo bhikkhu āpattiṃ āpajjitvā na icchati āpattiṃ paṭikātuṃ.**The monk Channa has committed an offense, but refuses to make amends for it.*";
P_HTM[1377]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya—**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should do a legal procedure of ejecting Channa for not making amends for an offense,*";
P_HTM[1378]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena.**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1379]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[1380]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1381]="*Ayaṃ channo bhikkhu āpattiṃ āpajjitvā na icchati āpattiṃ paṭikātuṃ.**The monk Channa has committed an offense, but refuses to make amends for it.*";
P_HTM[1382]="*Saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ karoti—**The Sangha is doing a legal procedure of ejecting Channa for not making amends for an offense,*";
P_HTM[1383]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena.**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1384]="*Yassāyasmato khamati channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyassa kammassa karaṇaṃ—**Any monk who approves of doing a legal procedure of ejecting Channa for not making amends for an offense,*";
P_HTM[1385]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena, so tuṇhassa;**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha, should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[1386]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[1387]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter …*";
P_HTM[1388]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—**For the third time I speak on this matter.*";
P_HTM[1389]="*suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1390]="*Ayaṃ channo bhikkhu āpattiṃ āpajjitvā na icchati āpattiṃ paṭikātuṃ.**The monk Channa has committed an offense, but refuses to make amends for it.*";
P_HTM[1391]="*Saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ karoti—**The Sangha is doing a legal procedure of ejecting Channa for not making amends for an offense,*";
P_HTM[1392]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena.**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1393]="*Yassāyasmato khamati channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyassa kammassa karaṇaṃ—**Any monk who approves of doing a legal procedure of ejecting Channa for not making amends for an offense,*";
P_HTM[1394]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena, so tuṇhassa;**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha, should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[1395]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[1396]="*Kataṃ saṅghena channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ—**The Sangha has done the legal procedure of ejecting Channa for not making amends for an offense,*";
P_HTM[1397]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena.**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1398]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[1399]="*Āvāsaparamparañca, bhikkhave, saṃsatha—**Monks, you should proclaim from monastery to monastery*";
P_HTM[1400]="*‘channo bhikkhu saṅghena āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammakato—**that the Sangha has done a legal procedure of ejecting Channa for not making amends for an offense,*";
P_HTM[1401]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghenā’ti.**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1402]="*6.1. Adhammakammadvādasaka**6.1 The group of twelve on illegitimate legal procedures*";
P_HTM[1403]="*Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgataṃ, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.**“When a legal procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has three qualities, it is illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[1404]="*Asammukhā kataṃ hoti, appaṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, appaṭiññāya kataṃ hoti—**it is done in the absence of the accused, it is done without questioning the accused, it is done without the admission of the accused.*";
P_HTM[1405]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[1406]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.**When a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[1407]="*Anāpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adesanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, desitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti …pe…**it is done against one who hasn’t committed any offense, it is done against one who has committed an offense that isn’t clearable by confession, it is done against one who has confessed their offense.*";
P_HTM[1408]="*acodetvā kataṃ hoti, asāretvā kataṃ hoti, āpattiṃ anāropetvā kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having accused the person of their offense, it is done without having reminded the person of their offense, it is done without having charged the person with their offense.*";
P_HTM[1409]="*asammukhā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done in the absence of the accused, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1410]="*appaṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without questioning the accused, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1411]="*appaṭiññāya kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without the admission of the accused, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1412]="*anāpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done against one who hasn’t committed any offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1413]="*adesanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done against one who has committed an offense that isn’t clearable by confession, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1414]="*desitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done against one who has confessed their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1415]="*acodetvā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having accused the person of their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1416]="*asāretvā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having reminded the person of their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1417]="*āpattiṃ anāropetvā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti—**When a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having charged the person with their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.”*";
P_HTM[1418]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[1419]="*Āpattiyā appaṭikamme ukkhepanīyakamme adhammakammadvādasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of twelve on illegitimate legal procedures of ejection for not making amends for an offense is finished.*";
P_HTM[1420]="*6.2. Dhammakammadvādasaka**6.2 The group of twelve on legitimate legal procedures*";
P_HTM[1421]="*Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgataṃ, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.**“When a legal procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has three qualities, it is legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[1422]="*Sammukhā kataṃ hoti, paṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, paṭiññāya kataṃ hoti—**it is done in the presence of the accused, it is done with the questioning of the accused, it is done with the admission of the accused.*";
P_HTM[1423]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[1424]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.**When a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[1425]="*Āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, desanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adesitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti …pe…**it is done against one who has committed an offense, it is done against one who has committed an offense that is clearable by confession, it is done against one who hasn’t confessed their offense.*";
P_HTM[1426]="*codetvā kataṃ hoti, sāretvā kataṃ hoti, āpattiṃ āropetvā kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done after having accused the person of their offense, it is done after having reminded the person of their offense, it is done after having charged the person with their offense.*";
P_HTM[1427]="*sammukhā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done in the presence of the accused, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1428]="*paṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done with the questioning of the accused, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1429]="*paṭiññāya kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done with the admission of the accused, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1430]="*āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done against one who has committed an offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1431]="*desanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done against one who has committed an offense that is clearable by confession, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1432]="*adesitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done against one who hasn’t confessed their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1433]="*codetvā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done after having accused the person of their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1434]="*sāretvā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done after having reminded the person of their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1435]="*āpattiṃ āropetvā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti—**When a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done after having charged the person with their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.”*";
P_HTM[1436]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[1437]="*Āpattiyā appaṭikamme ukkhepanīyakamme dhammakammadvādasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of twelve on legitimate legal procedures of ejection for not making amends for an offense is finished.*";
P_HTM[1438]="*6.3. Ākaṅkhamānachakka**6.3 The group of six on wishing*";
P_HTM[1439]="*Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**“When a monk has three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a legal procedure of ejecting him for not making amends for an offense:*";
P_HTM[1440]="*Bhaṇḍanakārako hoti kalahakārako vivādakārako bhassakārako saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako;**he is quarrelsome, argumentative, and a creator of legal issues in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[1441]="*bālo hoti abyatto āpattibahulo anapadāno;**he is ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, incapable of determining whether he has committed an offense;*";
P_HTM[1442]="*gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi—**he is constantly and improperly socializing with householders.*";
P_HTM[1443]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[1444]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**When a monk has another three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of ejecting him for not making amends for an offense:*";
P_HTM[1445]="*Adhisīle sīlavipanno hoti, ajjhācāre ācāravipanno hoti, atidiṭṭhiyā diṭṭhivipanno hoti—**he has failed in the higher morality; he has failed in conduct; he has failed in view.*";
P_HTM[1446]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[1447]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**When a monk has another three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of ejecting him for not making amends for an offense:*";
P_HTM[1448]="*Buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—**he disparages the Buddha; he disparages the Teaching; he disparages the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1449]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[1450]="*Tiṇṇaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**“The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense against three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[1451]="*Eko bhaṇḍanakārako hoti kalahakārako vivādakārako bhassakārako saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako;**those who are quarrelsome, argumentative, and creators of legal issues in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[1452]="*eko bālo hoti abyatto āpattibahulo anapadāno;**those who are ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, incapable of determining whether they have committed an offense;*";
P_HTM[1453]="*eko gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi—**those who are constantly and improperly socializing with householders.*";
P_HTM[1454]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[1455]="*Aparesampi, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense against another three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[1456]="*Eko adhisīle sīlavipanno hoti, eko ajjhācāre ācāravipanno hoti, eko atidiṭṭhiyā diṭṭhivipanno hoti—**those who have failed in the higher morality; those who have failed in conduct; those who have failed in view.*";
P_HTM[1457]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[1458]="*Aparesampi, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense against another three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[1459]="*Eko buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, eko dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, eko saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—**those who disparage the Buddha; those who disparage the Teaching; those who disparage the Sangha.”*";
P_HTM[1460]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[1461]="*Āpattiyā appaṭikamme ukkhepanīyakamme ākaṅkhamānachakkaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of six on wishing in regard to the legal procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense is finished.*";
P_HTM[1462]="*6.4. Tecattālīsavatta**6.4 The forty-three kinds of conduct*";
P_HTM[1463]="*Āpattiyā appaṭikamme ukkhepanīyakammakatena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā sammā vattitabbaṃ.**“A monk who has had a legal procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense done against himself should conduct himself properly.*";
P_HTM[1464]="*Tatrāyaṃ sammāvattanā—**This is the proper conduct:*";
P_HTM[1465]="*na upasampādetabbaṃ,**He should not give the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[1466]="*na nissayo dātabbo,**He should not give formal support.*";
P_HTM[1467]="*na sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo,**He should not have a novice monk attend on him.*";
P_HTM[1468]="*na bhikkhunovādakasammuti sāditabbā,**He should not accept being appointed as an instructor of the nuns.*";
P_HTM[1469]="*sammatenapi bhikkhuniyo na ovaditabbā.**Even if appointed, he should not instruct the nuns.*";
P_HTM[1470]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kataṃ hoti sā āpatti na āpajjitabbā,**He should not commit the same offense as the offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not making amends for an offense.*";
P_HTM[1471]="*aññā vā tādisikā,**He should not commit an offense similar to the offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not making amends for an offense.*";
P_HTM[1472]="*tato vā pāpiṭṭhatarā;**He should not commit an offense worse than the offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not making amends for an offense.*";
P_HTM[1473]="*kammaṃ na garahitabbaṃ,**He should not criticize the procedure.*";
P_HTM[1474]="*kammikā na garahitabbā.**He should not criticize those who did the procedure.*";
P_HTM[1475]="*Na pakatattassa bhikkhuno abhivādanaṃ,**He should not consent to a regular monk bowing down to him.*";
P_HTM[1476]="*paccuṭṭhānaṃ,**He should not consent to a regular monk standing up for him.*";
P_HTM[1477]="*añjalikammaṃ,**He should not consent to a regular monk raising his joined palms  to him.*";
P_HTM[1478]="*sāmīcikammaṃ,**He should not consent to a regular monk doing acts of respect toward him.*";
P_HTM[1479]="*āsanābhihāro,**He should not consent to a regular monk offering him a seat.*";
P_HTM[1480]="*seyyābhihāro,**He should not consent to a regular monk offering him a bed.*";
P_HTM[1481]="*pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ,**He should not consent to a regular monk offering him water for washing his feet and a foot stool.*";
P_HTM[1482]="*pādakathalikaṃ,**He should not consent to a regular monk offering him a foot scraper.*";
P_HTM[1483]="*pattacīvarappaṭiggahaṇaṃ,**He should not consent to a regular monk receiving his bowl and robe.*";
P_HTM[1484]="*nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ sāditabbaṃ.**He should not consent to a regular monk massaging his back when bathing.*";
P_HTM[1485]="*Na pakatatto bhikkhu sīlavipattiyā anuddhaṃsetabbo,**He should not charge a regular monk with failure in morality.*";
P_HTM[1486]="*na ācāravipattiyā anuddhaṃsetabbo,**He should not charge a regular monk with failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[1487]="*na diṭṭhivipattiyā anuddhaṃsetabbo,**He should not charge a regular monk with failure in view.*";
P_HTM[1488]="*na ājīvavipattiyā anuddhaṃsetabbo,**He should not charge a regular monk with failure in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[1489]="*na bhikkhu bhikkhūhi bhedetabbo.**He should not cause division between monks.*";
P_HTM[1490]="*Na gihiddhajo dhāretabbo,**He should not wear lay clothes.*";
P_HTM[1491]="*na titthiyaddhajo dhāretabbo,**He should not wear the robes of the monastics of other religions.*";
P_HTM[1492]="*na titthiyā sevitabbā;**He should not associate with the monastics of other religions.*";
P_HTM[1493]="*bhikkhū sevitabbā,**He should associate with monks.*";
P_HTM[1494]="*bhikkhusikkhāya sikkhitabbaṃ.**He should train in the monks’ training.*";
P_HTM[1495]="*Na pakatattena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ ekacchanne āvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not stay in the same room in a monastery as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[1496]="*na ekacchanne anāvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not stay in the same room in a non-monastery as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[1497]="*na ekacchanne āvāse vā anāvāse vā vatthabbaṃ,**He should not stay in the same room in a monastery or a non-monastery as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[1498]="*pakatattaṃ bhikkhuṃ disvā āsanā vuṭṭhātabbaṃ,**He should get up from his seat when he sees a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[1499]="*na pakatatto bhikkhu āsādetabbo anto vā bahi vā.**He should not dismiss a regular monk, whether inside or outside a dwelling.*";
P_HTM[1500]="*Na pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposatho ṭhapetabbo,**He should not cancel the observance-day procedure of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[1501]="*na pavāraṇā ṭhapetabbā,**He should not cancel the invitation procedure of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[1502]="*na savacanīyaṃ kātabbaṃ,**He should not speak to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him.*";
P_HTM[1503]="*na anuvādo paṭṭhapetabbo,**He should not make accusations against a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[1504]="*na okāso kāretabbo,**He should not ask a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense.*";
P_HTM[1505]="*na codetabbo,**He should not accuse a regular monk of an offense.*";
P_HTM[1506]="*na sāretabbo,**He should not remind a regular monk of an offense.*";
P_HTM[1507]="*na bhikkhūhi sampayojetabban”ti.**He should not associate inappropriately with other monks.”*";
P_HTM[1508]="*Āpattiyā appaṭikamme ukkhepanīyakamme tecattālīsavattaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The forty-three kinds of conduct in regard to the legal procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense are finished.*";
P_HTM[1509]="*Atha kho saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ akāsi—**Soon afterwards the Sangha did a legal procedure of ejecting the monk Channa for not making amends for an offense,*";
P_HTM[1510]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena.**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1511]="*So saṅghena, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammakato tamhā āvāsā aññaṃ āvāsaṃ agamāsi.**He then left that monastery and went to another one.*";
P_HTM[1512]="*Tattha bhikkhū neva abhivādesuṃ, na paccuṭṭhesuṃ, na añjalikammaṃ na sāmīcikammaṃ akaṃsu, na sakkariṃsu, na garuṃ kariṃsu, na mānesuṃ, na pūjesuṃ.**The monks there did not bow down to him, stand up for him, raise their joined palms to him, or do acts of respect toward him. They did not honor, respect, or esteem him.*";
P_HTM[1513]="*So bhikkhūhi asakkariyamāno agarukariyamāno amāniyamāno apūjiyamāno asakkārapakato tamhāpi āvāsā aññaṃ āvāsaṃ agamāsi.**Because of this, he left that monastery too and went to yet another one.*";
P_HTM[1514]="*Tatthapi bhikkhū neva abhivādesuṃ, na paccuṭṭhesuṃ, na añjalikammaṃ na sāmīcikammaṃ akaṃsu, na sakkariṃsu, na garuṃ kariṃsu, na mānesuṃ, na pūjesuṃ.**There too the monks did not bow down to him, stand up for him, raise their joined palms to him, or do acts of respect toward him. They did not honor, respect, or esteem him.*";
P_HTM[1515]="*So bhikkhūhi asakkariyamāno agarukariyamāno amāniyamāno apūjiyamāno asakkārapakato tamhāpi āvāsā aññaṃ āvāsaṃ agamāsi.**Because of this, he left that monastery too and went to yet another one.*";
P_HTM[1516]="*Tatthapi bhikkhū neva abhivādesuṃ, na paccuṭṭhesuṃ, na añjalikammaṃ na sāmīcikammaṃ akaṃsu, na sakkariṃsu, na garuṃ kariṃsu, na mānesuṃ, na pūjesuṃ.**There too the monks did not bow down to him, stand up for him, raise their joined palms to him, or do acts of respect toward him. They did not honor, respect, or esteem him.*";
P_HTM[1517]="*So bhikkhūhi asakkariyamāno agarukariyamāno amāniyamāno apūjiyamāno asakkārapakato punadeva kosambiṃ paccāgañchi.**Because of this, he left that monastery too and returned to Kosambī.*";
P_HTM[1518]="*So sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, bhikkhū upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeti—**He then conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released. He went to the monks*";
P_HTM[1519]="*“ahaṃ, āvuso, saṅghena, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammakato sammā vattāmi, lomaṃ pātemi, netthāraṃ vattāmi.**and told them about this,*";
P_HTM[1520]="*Kathaṃ nu kho mayā paṭipajjitabban”ti?**adding, “What should I do now?”*";
P_HTM[1521]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe….**The monks told the Buddha. He had the monks gathered and said,*";
P_HTM[1522]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetu.**“Well then, lift that legal procedure of ejecting the monk Channa for not making amends for an offense.*";
P_HTM[1523]="*6.5. Nappaṭippassambhetabbatecattālīsaka**6.5 The group of forty-three on not to be lifted*";
P_HTM[1524]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**“When a monk has five qualities, a legal procedure of ejecting him for not making amends for an offense should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1525]="*Upasampādeti, nissayaṃ deti, sāmaṇeraṃ upaṭṭhāpeti, bhikkhunovādakasammutiṃ sādiyati, sammatopi bhikkhuniyo ovadati—**he gives the full ordination; he gives formal support; he has a novice monk attend on him; he accepts being appointed as an instructor of the nuns; he instructs the nuns, whether appointed or not.*";
P_HTM[1526]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1527]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of ejecting him for not making amends for an offense should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1528]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kataṃ hoti taṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati, aññaṃ vā tādisikaṃ, tato vā pāpiṭṭhataraṃ;**he commits the same offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not making amends for an offense; he commits an offense similar to the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not making amends for an offense; he commits an offense worse than the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not making amends for an offense;*";
P_HTM[1529]="*kammaṃ garahati, kammike garahati …pe…**he criticizes the procedure; he criticizes those who did the procedure. …*";
P_HTM[1530]="*pakatattassa bhikkhuno abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ, añjalikammaṃ, sāmīcikammaṃ, āsanābhihāraṃ sādiyati …pe…**he consents to a regular monk bowing down to him; he consents to a regular monk standing up for him; he consents to a regular monk raising his joined palms to him; he consents to a regular monk doing acts of respect toward him; he consents to a regular monk offering him a seat. …*";
P_HTM[1531]="*pakatattassa bhikkhuno seyyābhihāraṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ, pādakathalikaṃ, pattacīvarappaṭiggahaṇaṃ, nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ sādiyati …pe…**he consents to a regular monk offering him a bed; he consents to a regular monk offering him water for washing his feet and a foot stool; he consents to a regular monk offering him a foot scraper; he consents to a regular monk receiving his bowl and robe; he consents to a regular monk massaging his back when bathing. …*";
P_HTM[1532]="*pakatattaṃ bhikkhuṃ sīlavipattiyā anuddhaṃseti, ācāravipattiyā anuddhaṃseti, diṭṭhivipattiyā anuddhaṃseti, ājīvavipattiyā anuddhaṃseti, bhikkhuṃ bhikkhūhi bhedeti …pe…**he charges a regular monk with failure in morality; he charges a regular monk with failure in conduct; he charges a regular monk with failure in view; he charges a regular monk with failure in livelihood; he causes division between monks. …*";
P_HTM[1533]="*gihiddhajaṃ dhāreti, titthiyaddhajaṃ dhāreti, titthiye sevati, bhikkhū na sevati, bhikkhusikkhāya na sikkhati …pe…**he wears lay clothes; he wears the robes of the monastics of other religions; he associates with the monastics of other religions; he doesn’t associate with monks; he doesn’t train in the monks’ training. …*";
P_HTM[1534]="*pakatattena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ ekacchanne āvāse vasati, ekacchanne anāvāse vasati, ekacchanne āvāse vā anāvāse vā vasati, pakatattaṃ bhikkhuṃ disvā āsanā na vuṭṭhāti, pakatattaṃ bhikkhuṃ āsādeti anto vā bahi vā—**he stays in the same room in a monastery as a regular monk; he stays in the same room in a non-monastery as a regular monk; he stays in the same room in a monastery or a non-monastery as a regular monk; he doesn’t get up from his seat when he sees a regular monk; he dismisses a regular monk, whether inside or outside a dwelling.*";
P_HTM[1535]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1536]="*Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has eight qualities, a procedure of ejecting him for not making amends for an offense should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1537]="*Pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposathaṃ ṭhapeti, pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapeti, savacanīyaṃ karoti, anuvādaṃ paṭṭhapeti, okāsaṃ kāreti, codeti, sāreti, bhikkhūhi sampayojeti—**he cancels the observance-day procedure of a regular monk; he cancels the invitation procedure of a regular monk; he speaks to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him; he makes accusations against a regular monk; he asks a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense; he accuses a regular monk of an offense; he reminds a regular monk of an offense; he associates inappropriately with other monks.”*";
P_HTM[1538]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1539]="*Āpattiyā appaṭikamme ukkhepanīyakamme nappaṭippassambhetabbatecattālīsakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of forty-three on not to be lifted in regard to the legal procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense is finished.*";
P_HTM[1540]="*6.6. Paṭippassambhetabbatecattālīsaka**6.6 The group of forty-three on to be lifted*";
P_HTM[1541]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**“When a monk has five qualities, a legal procedure of ejecting him for not making amends for an offense should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1542]="*Na upasampādeti, na nissayaṃ deti, na sāmaṇeraṃ upaṭṭhāpeti, na bhikkhunovādakasammutiṃ sādiyati, sammatopi bhikkhuniyo na ovadati—**he does not give the full ordination; he does not give formal support; he does not have a novice monk attend on him; he does not accept being appointed as an instructor of the nuns; he does not instruct the nuns, whether appointed or not.*";
P_HTM[1543]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1544]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of ejecting him for not making amends for an offense should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1545]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kataṃ hoti taṃ āpattiṃ na āpajjati, aññaṃ vā tādisikaṃ, tato vā pāpiṭṭhataraṃ;**he doesn’t commit the same offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not making amends for an offense; he doesn’t commit an offense similar to the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not making amends for an offense; he doesn’t commit an offense worse than the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not making amends for an offense;*";
P_HTM[1546]="*kammaṃ na garahati, kammike na garahati …pe…**he doesn’t criticize the procedure; he doesn’t criticize those who did the procedure. …*";
P_HTM[1547]="*na pakatattassa bhikkhuno abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ, añjalikammaṃ, sāmīcikammaṃ, āsanābhihāraṃ sādiyati …pe…**he doesn’t consent to a regular monk bowing down to him; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk standing up for him; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk raising his joined palms to him; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk doing acts of respect toward him; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk offering him a seat. …*";
P_HTM[1548]="*na pakatattassa bhikkhuno seyyābhihāraṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ, pādakathalikaṃ, pattacīvarappaṭiggahaṇaṃ, nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ sādiyati …pe…**he doesn’t consent to a regular monk offering him a bed; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk offering him water for washing his feet and a foot stool; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk offering him a foot scraper; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk receiving his bowl and robe; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk massaging his back when bathing. …*";
P_HTM[1549]="*na pakatattaṃ bhikkhuṃ sīlavipattiyā anuddhaṃseti, na ācāravipattiyā anuddhaṃseti, na diṭṭhivipattiyā anuddhaṃseti, na ājīvavipattiyā anuddhaṃseti, na bhikkhuṃ bhikkhūhi bhedeti …pe…**he doesn’t charge a regular monk with failure in morality; he doesn’t charge a regular monk with failure in conduct; he doesn’t charge a regular monk with failure in view; he doesn’t charge a regular monk with failure in livelihood; he doesn’t cause division between monks. …*";
P_HTM[1550]="*na gihiddhajaṃ dhāreti, na titthiyaddhajaṃ dhāreti, na titthiye sevati, bhikkhū sevati, bhikkhusikkhāya sikkhati …pe…**he doesn’t wear lay clothes; he doesn’t wear the robes of the monastics of other religions; he doesn’t associate with the monastics of other religions; he associates with monks; he trains in the monks’ training. …*";
P_HTM[1551]="*na pakatattena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ ekacchanne āvāse vasati, na ekacchanne anāvāse vasati, na ekacchanne āvāse vā anāvāse vā vasati, pakatattaṃ bhikkhuṃ disvā āsanā vuṭṭhāti, na pakatattaṃ bhikkhuṃ āsādeti anto vā bahi vā—**he doesn’t stay in the same room in a monastery as a regular monk; he doesn’t stay in the same room in a non-monastery as a regular monk; he doesn’t stay in the same room in a monastery or a non-monastery as a regular monk; he gets up from his seat when he sees a regular monk; he doesn’t dismiss a regular monk, whether inside or outside a dwelling.*";
P_HTM[1552]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1553]="*Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has eight qualities, a procedure of ejecting him for not making amends for an offense should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1554]="*Na pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposathaṃ ṭhapeti, na pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapeti, na savacanīyaṃ karoti, na anuvādaṃ paṭṭhapeti, na okāsaṃ kāreti, na codeti, na sāreti, na bhikkhūhi sampayojeti—**he doesn’t cancel the observance-day procedure of a regular monk; he doesn’t cancel the invitation procedure of a regular monk; he doesn’t speak to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him; he doesn’t make accusations against a regular monk; he doesn’t ask a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense; he doesn’t accuse a regular monk of an offense; he doesn’t remind a regular monk of an offense; he doesn’t associate inappropriately with other monks.”*";
P_HTM[1555]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1556]="*Āpattiyā appaṭikamme ukkhepanīyakamme paṭippassambhetabbatecattālīsakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of forty-three on to be lifted in regard to the legal procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense is finished.*";
P_HTM[1557]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**“And this is how it should be lifted.*";
P_HTM[1558]="*Tena bhikkhave, channena bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**The monk Channa should approach the Sangha, put his upper robes over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[1559]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, saṅghena āpattiyā appaṭikamme ukkhepanīyakammakato sammā vattāmi, lomaṃ pātemi, netthāraṃ vattāmi, āpattiyā appaṭikamme ukkhepanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācāmī’ti.**‘Venerables, the Sangha has done a legal procedure of ejecting me for not making amends for an offense, but I have conducted myself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released. I ask for the legal procedure of ejection to be lifted.’*";
P_HTM[1560]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbā.**And he should ask a second*";
P_HTM[1561]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[1562]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[1563]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1564]="*Ayaṃ channo bhikkhu saṅghena, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammakato sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, āpattiyā appaṭikamme ukkhepanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācati.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of ejecting the monk Channa for not making amends for an offense. He has conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now asks for the legal procedure of ejection to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[1565]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambheyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should lift the legal procedure of ejecting him for not making amends for an offense.*";
P_HTM[1566]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[1567]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1568]="*Ayaṃ channo bhikkhu saṅghena, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammakato sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, āpattiyā appaṭikamme ukkhepanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācati.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of ejecting the monk Channa for not making amends for an offense. He has conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now asks for the legal procedure of ejection to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[1569]="*Saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambheti.**The Sangha lifts the legal procedure of ejecting him for not making amends for an offense.*";
P_HTM[1570]="*Yassāyasmato khamati channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhi, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of lifting the legal procedure of ejecting the monk Channa for not making amends for an offense should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[1571]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[1572]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[1573]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—**For the third time I speak on this matter.*";
P_HTM[1574]="*suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1575]="*Ayaṃ channo bhikkhu saṅghena, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammakato sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācati.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of ejecting the monk Channa for not making amends for an offense. He has conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now asks for the legal procedure of ejection to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[1576]="*Saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambheti.**The Sangha lifts the legal procedure of ejecting him for not making amends for an offense.*";
P_HTM[1577]="*Yassāyasmato khamati channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhi, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of lifting the legal procedure of ejecting the monk Channa for not making amends for an offense should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[1578]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[1579]="*Paṭippassaddhaṃ saṅghena channassa bhikkhuno, āpattiyā appaṭikamme, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ.**The Sangha has lifted the legal procedure of ejecting the monk Channa for not making amends for an offense.*";
P_HTM[1580]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[1581]="*Āpattiyā appaṭikamme ukkhepanīyakammaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ.**The sixth section on the legal procedure of ejection for not making amends for an offense is finished.*";
P_HTM[1582]="*7. Pāpikāyadiṭṭhiyāappaṭinissagge ukkhepanīyakamma**7. The legal procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view*";
P_HTM[1583]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[1584]="*Tena kho pana samayena ariṭṭhassa nāma bhikkhuno gaddhabādhipubbassa evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ hoti—**At that time the monk Ariṭṭha, the ex-vulture-killer, had the following bad and erroneous view:*";
P_HTM[1585]="*“tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā”ti.**“As I understand the Teaching of the Buddha, the things he calls obstructive are not able to obstruct one who indulges in them.”*";
P_HTM[1586]="*Assosuṃ kho sambahulā bhikkhū ariṭṭhassa nāma kira bhikkhuno gaddhabādhipubbassa evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ—**A number of monks heard that Ariṭṭha had that view.*";
P_HTM[1587]="*“Tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[1588]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū yena ariṭṭho bhikkhu gaddhabādhipubbo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu.**They went to him*";
P_HTM[1589]="*Upasaṅkamitvā ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ etadavocuṃ—**and asked,*";
P_HTM[1590]="*“saccaṃ kira te, āvuso ariṭṭha, evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ—**“Is it true, Ariṭṭha, that you have such a view?”*";
P_HTM[1591]="*tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[1592]="*“Evaṃ byā kho ahaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā”ti.**“Yes, indeed. As I understand the Buddha’s Teaching, the things he calls obstructive are not able to obstruct one who indulges in them.”*";
P_HTM[1593]="*“Māvuso ariṭṭha, evaṃ avaca.**“No, Ariṭṭha,*";
P_HTM[1594]="*Mā bhagavantaṃ abbhācikkhi.**don’t misrepresent the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[1595]="*Na hi sādhu bhagavato abbhakkhānaṃ.**for it’s not good to misrepresent him.*";
P_HTM[1596]="*Na hi bhagavā evaṃ vadeyya.**The Buddha would never say such a thing.*";
P_HTM[1597]="*Anekapariyāyenāvuso ariṭṭha, antarāyikā dhammā antarāyikā vuttā bhagavatā.**The Buddha has given many discourses about the obstructive things being obstructive*";
P_HTM[1598]="*Alañca pana te paṭisevato antarāyāya.**and how they obstruct one who indulges in them.*";
P_HTM[1599]="*Appassādā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā, bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo.**The Buddha has said that there is little enjoyment in worldly pleasures, but much suffering and much trouble, and that the danger in them is greater.*";
P_HTM[1600]="*Aṭṭhikaṅkalūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā, bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo.**The Buddha has said that worldly pleasures are similar to a skeleton,*";
P_HTM[1601]="*Maṃsapesūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …pe…**similar to a piece of meat,*";
P_HTM[1602]="*tiṇukkūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …pe…**similar to a grass torch,*";
P_HTM[1603]="*aṅgārakāsūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …**similar to a pit of coals,*";
P_HTM[1604]="*supinakūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …**similar to a dream,*";
P_HTM[1605]="*yācitakūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …**similar to borrowed goods,*";
P_HTM[1606]="*rukkhaphalūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …**similar to fruits on a tree,*";
P_HTM[1607]="*asisūnūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …**similar to a knife and chopping block,*";
P_HTM[1608]="*sattisūlūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …**similar to swords and stakes,*";
P_HTM[1609]="*sappasirūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā, bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo”ti.**and similar to a snake’s head; they are much suffering and much trouble, and the danger in them is greater.”*";
P_HTM[1610]="*Evampi kho ariṭṭho bhikkhu gaddhabādhipubbo tehi bhikkhūhi vuccamāno tatheva taṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ thāmasā parāmāsā abhinivissa voharati—**But even though the monks corrected Ariṭṭha in this way, he stubbornly held on to that bad and erroneous view, and continued to insist on it.*";
P_HTM[1611]="*“evaṃ byā kho ahaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[1612]="*Yato ca kho te bhikkhū nāsakkhiṃsu ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ etasmā pāpakā diṭṭhigatā vivecetuṃ, atha kho te bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**And since they were not able to make him give up that view, they went to the Buddha and told him what had happened.*";
P_HTM[1613]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned Ariṭṭha:*";
P_HTM[1614]="*“saccaṃ kira te, ariṭṭha, evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ—**“Is it true, Ariṭṭha, that you have a bad and erroneous view such as this:*";
P_HTM[1615]="*tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā”ti?**‘As I understand the Buddha’s Teaching, the things he calls obstructive are not able to obstruct one who indulges in them’?”*";
P_HTM[1616]="*“Evaṃ byā kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā”ti.**“Yes indeed, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[1617]="*“Kassa nu kho nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, mayā evaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāsi?**“Foolish man, who do you think I have taught like this?*";
P_HTM[1618]="*Nanu mayā, moghapurisa, anekapariyāyena antarāyikā dhammā antarāyikā vuttā?**Haven’t I given many discourses about the obstructive things being obstructive*";
P_HTM[1619]="*Alañca pana te paṭisevato antarāyāya.**and how they obstruct one who indulges in them?*";
P_HTM[1620]="*Appassādā kāmā vuttā mayā, bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo.**I have said that there is little enjoyment in worldly pleasures, but much suffering and much trouble, and that the danger in them is greater.*";
P_HTM[1621]="*Aṭṭhikaṅkalūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā, bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo.**I have said that worldly pleasures are similar to a skeleton …*";
P_HTM[1622]="*Maṃsapesūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …pe…**similar to a piece of meat …*";
P_HTM[1623]="*tiṇukkūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**similar to a grass torch …*";
P_HTM[1624]="*aṅgārakāsūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**similar to a pit of coals …*";
P_HTM[1625]="*supinakūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**similar to a dream …*";
P_HTM[1626]="*yācitakūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**similar to borrowed goods …*";
P_HTM[1627]="*rukkhaphalūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**similar to fruits on a tree …*";
P_HTM[1628]="*asisūnūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**similar to a knife and chopping block …*";
P_HTM[1629]="*sattisūlūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**similar to swords and stakes …*";
P_HTM[1630]="*sappasirūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā, bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo.**similar to a snake’s head; they are much suffering and much trouble, and the danger in them is greater.*";
P_HTM[1631]="*Atha ca pana tvaṃ, moghapurisa, attanā duggahitena amhe ceva abbhācikkhasi, attānañca khaṇasi, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavasi.**And yet by misunderstanding, you have misrepresented me, hurt yourself, and made much demerit.*";
P_HTM[1632]="*Tañhi te, moghapurisa, bhavissati dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya.**This will be for your long-lasting harm and suffering.*";
P_HTM[1633]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[1634]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**and after rebuking him …*";
P_HTM[1635]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[1636]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho ariṭṭhassa bhikkhuno gaddhabādhipubbassa, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ karotu—**“Well then, the Sangha should do a legal procedure of ejecting Ariṭṭha for not giving up a bad view,*";
P_HTM[1637]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena.**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1638]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, kātabbaṃ—**And this is how it should be done.*";
P_HTM[1639]="*paṭhamaṃ ariṭṭho bhikkhu codetabbo, codetvā sāretabbo, sāretvā āpattiṃ āropetabbo, āpattiṃ āropetvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**First you should accuse the monk Ariṭṭha. He should then be reminded of what he has done, before he is charged with an offense. A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[1640]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1641]="*Ariṭṭhassa bhikkhuno gaddhabādhipubbassa evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ—**The monk Ariṭṭha, the ex-vulture-killer, has the following bad and erroneous view:*";
P_HTM[1642]="*tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyāti.**“As I understand the Teaching of the Buddha, the things he calls obstructive are not able to obstruct one who indulges in them.”*";
P_HTM[1643]="*So taṃ diṭṭhiṃ na paṭinissajjati.**He is not giving up that view.*";
P_HTM[1644]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho ariṭṭhassa bhikkhuno gaddhabādhipubbassa, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya—**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should do a legal procedure of ejecting Ariṭṭha for not giving up a bad view,*";
P_HTM[1645]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena.**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1646]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[1647]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1648]="*Ariṭṭhassa bhikkhuno gaddhabādhipubbassa evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ—**The monk Ariṭṭha, the ex-vulture-killer, has the following bad and erroneous view:*";
P_HTM[1649]="*tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyāti.**“As I understand the Teaching of the Buddha, the things he calls obstructive are not able to obstruct one who indulges in them.”*";
P_HTM[1650]="*So taṃ diṭṭhiṃ na paṭinissajjati.**He is not giving up that view.*";
P_HTM[1651]="*Saṅgho ariṭṭhassa bhikkhuno gaddhabādhipubbassa, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ karoti—**The Sangha is doing a legal procedure of ejecting Ariṭṭha for not giving up a bad view,*";
P_HTM[1652]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena.**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1653]="*Yassāyasmato khamati ariṭṭhassa bhikkhuno gaddhabādhipubbassa, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyassa kammassa karaṇaṃ—**Any monk who approves of doing a legal procedure of ejecting Ariṭṭha for not giving up a bad view,*";
P_HTM[1654]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena, so tuṇhassa;**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha, should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[1655]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[1656]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter …*";
P_HTM[1657]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—**For the third time I speak on this matter.*";
P_HTM[1658]="*suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1659]="*Ariṭṭhassa bhikkhuno gaddhabādhipubbassa evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ—**The monk Ariṭṭha, the ex-vulture-killer, has the following bad and erroneous view:*";
P_HTM[1660]="*tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyāti.**“As I understand the Teaching of the Buddha, the things he calls obstructive are not able to obstruct one who indulges in them.”*";
P_HTM[1661]="*So taṃ diṭṭhiṃ na paṭinissajjati.**He is not giving up that view.*";
P_HTM[1662]="*Saṅgho ariṭṭhassa bhikkhuno gaddhabādhipubbassa, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ karoti—**The Sangha is doing a legal procedure of ejecting Ariṭṭha for not giving up a bad view,*";
P_HTM[1663]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena.**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1664]="*Yassāyasmato khamati ariṭṭhassa bhikkhuno gaddhabādhipubbassa, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyassa kammassa karaṇaṃ—**Any monk who approves of doing a legal procedure of ejecting Ariṭṭha for not giving up a bad view,*";
P_HTM[1665]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena, so tuṇhassa;**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha, should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[1666]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[1667]="*Kataṃ saṅghena ariṭṭhassa bhikkhuno gaddhabādhipubbassa, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ—**The Sangha has done the legal procedure of ejecting Ariṭṭha for not giving up a bad view,*";
P_HTM[1668]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena.**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1669]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[1670]="*Āvāsaparamparañca, bhikkhave, saṃsatha—**Monks, you should proclaim from monastery to monastery*";
P_HTM[1671]="*‘ariṭṭho bhikkhu gaddhabādhipubbo, saṅghena pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammakato—**that the Sangha has done a legal procedure of ejecting Ariṭṭha for not giving up a bad view,*";
P_HTM[1672]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghenā’”ti.**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1673]="*7.1. Adhammakammadvādasaka**7.1 The group of twelve on illegitimate legal procedures*";
P_HTM[1674]="*“Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgataṃ, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.**“When a legal procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has three qualities, it is illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[1675]="*Asammukhā kataṃ hoti, appaṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, appaṭiññāya kataṃ hoti—**it is done in the absence of the accused, it is done without questioning the accused, it is done without the admission of the accused.*";
P_HTM[1676]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[1677]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.**When a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[1678]="*Anāpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adesanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, desitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti …pe…**it is done against one who hasn’t committed any offense, it is done against one who has committed an offense that isn’t clearable by confession, it is done against one who has confessed their offense.*";
P_HTM[1679]="*acodetvā kataṃ hoti, asāretvā kataṃ hoti, āpattiṃ anāropetvā kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having accused the person of their offense, it is done without having reminded the person of their offense, it is done without having charged the person with their offense.*";
P_HTM[1680]="*asammukhā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done in the absence of the accused, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1681]="*appaṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without questioning the accused, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1682]="*appaṭiññāya kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without the admission of the accused, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1683]="*anāpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done against one who hasn’t committed any offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1684]="*adesanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done against one who has committed an offense that isn’t clearable by confession, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1685]="*desitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done against one who has confessed their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1686]="*acodetvā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having accused the person of their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1687]="*asāretvā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having reminded the person of their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[1688]="*āpattiṃ anāropetvā kataṃ hoti, adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti—**When a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having charged the person with their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.”*";
P_HTM[1689]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[1690]="*Pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge ukkhepanīyakamme adhammakammadvādasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of twelve on illegitimate legal procedures of ejection for not giving up a bad view is finished.*";
P_HTM[1691]="*7.2. Dhammakammadvādasaka**7.2 The group of twelve on legitimate legal procedures*";
P_HTM[1692]="*Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgataṃ, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.**“When a legal procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has three qualities, it is legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[1693]="*Sammukhā kataṃ hoti, paṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, paṭiññāya kataṃ hoti—**it is done in the presence of the accused, it is done with the questioning of the accused, it is done with the admission of the accused.*";
P_HTM[1694]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[1695]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.**When a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[1696]="*Āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, desanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, adesitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti …pe…**it is done against one who has committed an offense, it is done against one who has committed an offense that is clearable by confession, it is done against one who hasn’t confessed their offense.*";
P_HTM[1697]="*codetvā kataṃ hoti, sāretvā kataṃ hoti, āpattiṃ āropetvā kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done after having accused the person of their offense, it is done after having reminded the person of their offense, it is done after having charged the person with their offense.*";
P_HTM[1698]="*sammukhā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done in the presence of the accused, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1699]="*paṭipucchā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done with the questioning of the accused, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1700]="*paṭiññāya kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done with the admission of the accused, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1701]="*āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done against one who has committed an offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1702]="*desanāgāminiyā āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done against one who has committed an offense that is clearable by confession, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1703]="*adesitāya āpattiyā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done against one who hasn’t confessed their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1704]="*codetvā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**“When a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done after having accused the person of their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1705]="*sāretvā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti …pe…**When a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done after having reminded the person of their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[1706]="*āpattiṃ āropetvā kataṃ hoti, dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti—**When a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done after having charged the person with their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.”*";
P_HTM[1707]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[1708]="*Pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge ukkhepanīyakamme dhammakammadvādasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of twelve on legitimate legal procedures of ejection for not giving up a bad view is finished.*";
P_HTM[1709]="*7.3. Ākaṅkhamānachakka**7.3 The group of six on wishing*";
P_HTM[1710]="*Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**“When a monk has three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a legal procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view:*";
P_HTM[1711]="*Bhaṇḍanakārako hoti kalahakārako vivādakārako bhassakārako saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako;**he is quarrelsome, argumentative, and a creator of legal issues in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[1712]="*bālo hoti abyatto āpattibahulo anapadāno;**he is ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, incapable of determining whether he has committed an offense;*";
P_HTM[1713]="*gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi—**he is constantly and improperly socializing with householders.*";
P_HTM[1714]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[1715]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**When a monk has another three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view:*";
P_HTM[1716]="*Adhisīle sīlavipanno hoti, ajjhācāre ācāravipanno hoti, atidiṭṭhiyā diṭṭhivipanno hoti—**he has failed in the higher morality; he has failed in conduct; he has failed in view.*";
P_HTM[1717]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[1718]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**When a monk has another three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view:*";
P_HTM[1719]="*Buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—**he disparages the Buddha; he disparages the Teaching; he disparages the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1720]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[1721]="*Tiṇṇaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**“The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view against three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[1722]="*Eko bhaṇḍanakārako hoti kalahakārako vivādakārako bhassakārako saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako;**those who are quarrelsome, argumentative, and creators of legal issues in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[1723]="*eko bālo hoti abyatto āpattibahulo anapadāno;**those who are ignorant and incompetent, often committing offenses, incapable of determining whether they have committed an offense;*";
P_HTM[1724]="*eko gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi—**those who are constantly and improperly socializing with householders.*";
P_HTM[1725]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[1726]="*Aparesampi, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view against another three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[1727]="*Eko adhisīle sīlavipanno hoti, eko ajjhācāre ācāravipanno hoti, eko atidiṭṭhiyā diṭṭhivipanno hoti—**those who have failed in the higher morality; those who have failed in conduct; those who have failed in view.*";
P_HTM[1728]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[1729]="*Aparesampi, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.**The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view against another three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[1730]="*Eko buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, eko dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, eko saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—**those who disparage the Buddha; those who disparage the Teaching; those who disparage the Sangha.”*";
P_HTM[1731]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissage, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[1732]="*Pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissage ukkhepanīyakamme ākaṅkhamānachakkaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of six on wishing in regard to the legal procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view is finished.*";
P_HTM[1733]="*7.4. Tecattālīsavatta**7.4 The forty-three kinds of conduct*";
P_HTM[1734]="*Pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge ukkhepanīyakammakatena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā sammā vattitabbaṃ.**“A monk who has had a legal procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view done against himself should conduct himself properly.*";
P_HTM[1735]="*Tatrāyaṃ sammāvattanā—**This is the proper conduct:*";
P_HTM[1736]="*na upasampādetabbaṃ,**He should not give the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[1737]="*na nissayo dātabbo,**He should not give formal support.*";
P_HTM[1738]="*na sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo,**He should not have a novice monk attend on him.*";
P_HTM[1739]="*na bhikkhunovādakasammuti sāditabbā,**He should not accept being appointed as an instructor of the nuns.*";
P_HTM[1740]="*sammatenapi bhikkhuniyo na ovaditabbā.**Even if appointed, he should not instruct the nuns.*";
P_HTM[1741]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kataṃ hoti sā āpatti na āpajjitabbā,**He should not commit the same offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view;*";
P_HTM[1742]="*aññā vā tādisikā,**He should not commit an offense similar to the offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view;*";
P_HTM[1743]="*tato vā pāpiṭṭhatarā;**He should not commit an offense worse than the offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view;*";
P_HTM[1744]="*kammaṃ na garahitabbaṃ,**He should not criticize the procedure.*";
P_HTM[1745]="*kammikā na garahitabbā …pe…,**He should not criticize those who did the procedure.*";
P_HTM[1746]="*na pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposatho ṭhapetabbo,**He should not cancel the observance-day procedure of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[1747]="*na pavāraṇā ṭhapetabbā,**He should not cancel the invitation procedure of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[1748]="*na savacanīyaṃ kātabbaṃ,**He should not speak to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him.*";
P_HTM[1749]="*na anuvādo paṭṭhapetabbo,**He should not make accusations against a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[1750]="*na okāso kāretabbo,**He should not ask a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense.*";
P_HTM[1751]="*na codetabbo,**He should not accuse a regular monk of an offense.*";
P_HTM[1752]="*na sāretabbo,**He should not remind a regular monk of an offense.*";
P_HTM[1753]="*na bhikkhūhi sampayojetabban”ti.**He should not associate inappropriately with other monks.”*";
P_HTM[1754]="*Pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge ukkhepanīyakamme tecattālīsavattaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The forty-three kinds of conduct in regard to the legal procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view are finished.*";
P_HTM[1755]="*Atha kho saṅgho ariṭṭhassa bhikkhuno gaddhabādhipubbassa, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ akāsi—**Soon afterwards the Sangha did a legal procedure of ejecting Ariṭṭha for not giving up a bad view,*";
P_HTM[1756]="*asambhogaṃ saṅghena.**prohibiting him from living with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1757]="*So saṅghena, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammakato vibbhami.**He then disrobed.*";
P_HTM[1758]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[1759]="*“kathañhi nāma ariṭṭho bhikkhu gaddhabādhipubbo saṅghena, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammakato vibbhamissatī”ti?**“How could the monk Ariṭṭha disrobe after the Sangha had done a legal procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view?”*";
P_HTM[1760]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**The monks told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[1761]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[1762]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, ariṭṭho bhikkhu gaddhabādhipubbo saṅghena, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammakato vibbhamatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the monk Ariṭṭha disrobed after the Sangha had done a procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view?”*";
P_HTM[1763]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[1764]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—**The Buddha criticized him …*";
P_HTM[1765]="*“ananucchavikaṃ …pe…**“It’s not suitable …*";
P_HTM[1766]="*kathañhi nāma so, bhikkhave, moghapuriso saṅghena, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammakato vibbhamissati?**How can that fool disrobe after the Sangha has done a procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view?*";
P_HTM[1767]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[1768]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing him …*";
P_HTM[1769]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[1770]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetu.**“Well then, the Sangha should lift that legal procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view.*";
P_HTM[1771]="*7.5. Nappaṭippassambhetabbatecattālīsaka**7.5 The group of forty-three on not to be lifted*";
P_HTM[1772]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**“When a monk has five qualities, a legal procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1773]="*Upasampādeti, nissayaṃ deti, sāmaṇeraṃ upaṭṭhāpeti, bhikkhunovādakasammutiṃ sādiyati, sammatopi bhikkhuniyo ovadati—**he gives the full ordination; he gives formal support; he has a novice monk attend on him; he accepts being appointed as an instructor of the nuns; he instructs the nuns, whether appointed or not.*";
P_HTM[1774]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissage, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1775]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1776]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kataṃ hoti taṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati, aññaṃ vā tādisikaṃ, tato vā pāpiṭṭhataraṃ;**he commits the same offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view; he commits an offense similar to the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view; he commits an offense worse than the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view;*";
P_HTM[1777]="*kammaṃ garahati, kammike garahati—**he criticizes the procedure; he criticizes those who did the procedure. …*";
P_HTM[1778]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[1779]="*pe….**he consents to a regular monk bowing down to him; he consents to a regular monk standing up for him; he consents to a regular monk raising his joined palms to him; he consents to a regular monk doing appropriate duties for him; he consents to a regular monk offering him a seat. … he consents to a regular monk offering him a bed; he consents to a regular monk offering him water for washing his feet and a foot stool; he consents to a regular monk offering him a foot scraper; he consents to a regular monk receiving his bowl and robe; he consents to a regular monk massaging his back when bathing. … he charges a regular monk with failure in morality; he charges a regular monk with failure in conduct; he charges a regular monk with failure in view; he charges a regular monk with failure in livelihood; he causes splits between monks. … he wears lay clothes; he wears the robes of the monastics of other religions; he associates with the monastics of other religions; he doesn’t associate with monks; he doesn’t train in the monks’ training. … he stays in the same room in a monastery as a regular monk; he stays in the same room in a non-monastery as a regular monk; he stays in the same room in a monastery or a non-monastery as a regular monk; he doesn’t get up from his seat when he sees a regular monk; he dismisses a regular monk, whether inside or outside a dwelling.*";
P_HTM[1780]="*Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has eight qualities, a procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view should not be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1781]="*Pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposathaṃ ṭhapeti, pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapeti, savacanīyaṃ karoti, anuvādaṃ paṭṭhapeti, okāsaṃ kāreti, codeti, sāreti, bhikkhūhi sampayojeti—**he cancels the observance-day procedure of a regular monk; he cancels the invitation procedure of a regular monk; he speaks to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him; he makes accusations against a regular monk; he asks a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense; he accuses a regular monk of an offense; he reminds a regular monk of an offense; he associates inappropriately with other monks.”*";
P_HTM[1782]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ nappaṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1783]="*Pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge ukkhepanīyakamme nappaṭippassambhetabbatecattālīsakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of forty-three on not to be lifted in regard to the legal procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view is finished.*";
P_HTM[1784]="*7.6. Paṭippassambhetabbatecattālīsaka**7.6 The group of forty-three on to be lifted*";
P_HTM[1785]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**“When a monk has five qualities, a legal procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1786]="*Na upasampādeti, na nissayaṃ deti, na sāmaṇeraṃ upaṭṭhāpeti, na bhikkhunovādakasammutiṃ sādiyati, sammatopi bhikkhuniyo na ovadati—**he does not give the full ordination; he does not give formal support; he does not have a novice monk attend on him; he does not accept being appointed as an instructor of the nuns; he does not instruct the nuns, whether appointed or not.*";
P_HTM[1787]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1788]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has another five qualities, a procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1789]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kataṃ hoti taṃ āpattiṃ na āpajjati, aññaṃ vā tādisikaṃ, tato vā pāpiṭṭhataraṃ;**he doesn’t commit the same offense as the offense for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view; he doesn’t commit an offense similar to the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view; he doesn’t commit an offense worse than the one for which the Sangha did the procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view;*";
P_HTM[1790]="*kammaṃ na garahati, kammike na garahati—**he doesn’t criticize the procedure; he doesn’t criticize those who did the procedure. …*";
P_HTM[1791]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[1792]="*pe….**he doesn’t consent to a regular monk bowing down to him; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk standing up for him; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk raising his joined palms to him; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk doing appropriate duties for him; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk offering him a seat. … he doesn’t consent to a regular monk offering him a bed; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk offering him water for washing his feet and a foot stool; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk offering him a foot scraper; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk receiving his bowl and robe; he doesn’t consent to a regular monk massaging his back when bathing. … he doesn’t charge a regular monk with failure in morality; he doesn’t charge a regular monk with failure in conduct; he doesn’t charge a regular monk with failure in view; he doesn’t charge a regular monk with failure in livelihood; he doesn’t cause splits between monks. … he doesn’t wear lay clothes; he doesn’t wear the robes of the monastics of other religions; he doesn’t associate with the monastics of other religions; he associates with monks; he trains in the monks’ training. … he doesn’t stay in the same room in a monastery as a regular monk; he doesn’t stay in the same room in a non-monastery as a regular monk; he doesn’t stay in the same room in a monastery or a non-monastery as a regular monk; he gets up from his seat when he sees a regular monk; he doesn’t dismiss a regular monk, whether inside or outside a dwelling.*";
P_HTM[1793]="*Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**When a monk has eight qualities, a procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view should be lifted:*";
P_HTM[1794]="*Na pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposathaṃ ṭhapeti, na pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapeti, na savacanīyaṃ karoti, na anuvādaṃ paṭṭhapeti, na okāsaṃ kāreti, na codeti, na sāreti, na bhikkhūhi sampayojeti—**he doesn’t cancel the observance-day procedure of a regular monk; he doesn’t cancel the invitation procedure of a regular monk; he doesn’t speak to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him; he doesn’t make accusations against a regular monk; he doesn’t ask a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense; he doesn’t accuse a regular monk of an offense; he doesn’t remind a regular monk of an offense; he doesn’t associate inappropriately with other monks.”*";
P_HTM[1795]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1796]="*Pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge ukkhepanīyakamme paṭippassambhetabbatecattālīsakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of forty-three on to be lifted in regard to the legal procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view is finished.*";
P_HTM[1797]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, paṭippassambhetabbaṃ.**“And, monks, this is how it should be lifted.*";
P_HTM[1798]="*Tena, bhikkhave, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammakatena bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**The monk who has been ejected by the Sangha for not giving up a bad view should approach the Sangha, put his upper robes over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[1799]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, saṅghena, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammakato sammā vattāmi, lomaṃ pātemi, netthāraṃ vattāmi, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācāmī’ti.**‘Venerables, the Sangha has done a legal procedure of ejecting me for not giving up a bad view, but I have conducted myself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released. I ask for the legal procedure of ejection to be lifted.’*";
P_HTM[1800]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbā.**And he should ask a second*";
P_HTM[1801]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[1802]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[1803]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1804]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu saṅghena, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammakato sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācati.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of ejecting monk so-and-so for not giving up a bad view. He has conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now asks for the legal procedure of ejection to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[1805]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambheyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should lift the legal procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view.*";
P_HTM[1806]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[1807]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1808]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu saṅghena, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammakato sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācati.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of ejecting monk so-and-so for not giving up a bad view. He has conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now asks for the legal procedure of ejection to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[1809]="*Saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambheti.**The Sangha lifts the legal procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view.*";
P_HTM[1810]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhi, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of lifting the legal procedure of ejecting monk so-and-so for not giving up a bad view should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[1811]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[1812]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[1813]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—**For the third time I speak on this matter.*";
P_HTM[1814]="*suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1815]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu saṅghena, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammakato sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge ukkhepanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhiṃ yācati.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of ejecting monk so-and-so for not giving up a bad view. He has conducted himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and now asks for the legal procedure of ejection to be lifted.*";
P_HTM[1816]="*Saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ paṭippassambheti.**The Sangha lifts the legal procedure of ejecting him for not giving up a bad view.*";
P_HTM[1817]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyassa kammassa paṭippassaddhi, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of lifting the legal procedure of ejecting monk so-and-so for not giving up a bad view should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[1818]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[1819]="*Paṭippassaddhaṃ saṅghena itthannāmassa bhikkhuno, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge, ukkhepanīyakammaṃ.**The Sangha has lifted the legal procedure of ejecting monk so-and-so for not giving up a bad view.*";
P_HTM[1820]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[1821]="*Pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge ukkhepanīyakammaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ.**The seventh section on the legal procedure of ejection for not giving up a bad view is finished.*";
P_HTM[1822]="*Kammakkhandhako paṭhamo. Imamhi khandhake vatthū satta.**The first chapter on legal procedures is finished. In this chapter there are seven topics.*";
