P_HTM[1959]="*2. Pārivāsikakkhandhaka **2.  The chapter on those on probation *";
P_HTM[1960]="*1. Pārivāsikavatta**1. The proper conduct of those on probation*";
P_HTM[1961]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[1962]="*Tena kho pana samayena pārivāsikā bhikkhū sādiyanti pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ, añjalikammaṃ, sāmīcikammaṃ, āsanābhihāraṃ, seyyābhihāraṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ, pādakathalikaṃ, pattacīvarappaṭiggahaṇaṃ, nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ.**At that time monks on probation consented to regular monks bowing down to them, standing up for them, raising their joined palms to them, doing acts of respect toward them, offering them a seat, offering them a bed, offering them water for washing their feet and a foot stool, offering them a foot scraper, receiving their bowl and robe, and massaging their backs when bathing.*";
P_HTM[1963]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[1964]="*“kathañhi nāma pārivāsikā bhikkhū sādiyissanti pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ, añjalikammaṃ, sāmīcikammaṃ, āsanābhihāraṃ, seyyābhihāraṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ, pādakathalikaṃ, pattacīvarappaṭiggahaṇaṃ, nahāne piṭṭhiparikamman”ti.**“How can monks on probation consent to these things?”*";
P_HTM[1965]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**The monks told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[1966]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[1967]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, pārivāsikā bhikkhū sādiyanti pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ, añjalikammaṃ, sāmīcikammaṃ, āsanābhihāraṃ, seyyābhihāraṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ, pādakathalikaṃ, pattacīvarappaṭiggahaṇaṃ, nahāne piṭṭhiparikamman”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that monks on probation consent to these things?”*";
P_HTM[1968]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[1969]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[1970]="*“ananucchavikaṃ …pe…**“It’s not suitable …*";
P_HTM[1971]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, pārivāsikā bhikkhū sādiyissanti pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ, añjalikammaṃ, sāmīcikammaṃ, āsanābhihāraṃ, seyyābhihāraṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ, pādakathalikaṃ, pattacīvarappaṭiggahaṇaṃ, nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ.**How can monks on probation consent to these things?*";
P_HTM[1972]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[1973]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[1974]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[1975]="*“na, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā sāditabbaṃ**“A monk on probation should not consent to:*";
P_HTM[1976]="*pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ,**Regular monks bowing down to him;*";
P_HTM[1977]="*paccuṭṭhānaṃ,**Regular monks standing up for him;*";
P_HTM[1978]="*añjalikammaṃ,**Regular monks raising their joined palms to him;*";
P_HTM[1979]="*sāmīcikammaṃ,**Regular monks doing acts of respect toward him;*";
P_HTM[1980]="*āsanābhihāro,**Regular monks offering him a seat;*";
P_HTM[1981]="*seyyābhihāro,**Regular monks offering him a bed;*";
P_HTM[1982]="*pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ,**Regular monks offering him water for washing his feet and a foot stool;*";
P_HTM[1983]="*pādakathalikaṃ,**Regular monks offering him a foot scraper;*";
P_HTM[1984]="*pattacīvarappaṭiggahaṇaṃ,**Regular monks receiving his bowl and robe;*";
P_HTM[1985]="*nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ.**Regular monks massaging his back when he is bathing.*";
P_HTM[1986]="*Yo sādiyeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he consents to any of these, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1987]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pārivāsikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ mithu yathāvuḍḍhaṃ abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ, añjalikammaṃ, sāmīcikammaṃ, āsanābhihāraṃ, seyyābhihāraṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ, pādakathalikaṃ, pattacīvarappaṭiggahaṇaṃ, nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ.**Monks on probation should bow down to one another according to seniority, and likewise stand up, raise their joined palms, do acts of respect, offer a seat, offer a bed, offer water for washing the feet and a foot stool, offer a foot scraper, receive bowl and robe, and massage one another’s backs according to seniority when bathing.*";
P_HTM[1988]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pārivāsikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pañca yathāvuḍḍhaṃ—**Monks on probation should do five things with regular monks according to seniority:*";
P_HTM[1989]="*uposathaṃ, pavāraṇaṃ, vassikasāṭikaṃ, oṇojanaṃ, bhattaṃ.**the observance-day procedure, the invitation procedure, the sharing out of rainy-season robes, meal invitations, and meals.*";
P_HTM[1990]="*Tena hi, bhikkhave, pārivāsikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ vattaṃ paññapessāmi yathā pārivāsikehi bhikkhūhi vattitabbaṃ.**And I will lay down the proper conduct for a monk on probation.*";
P_HTM[1991]="*Pārivāsikena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā sammā vattitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1992]="*Tatrāyaṃ sammāvattanā—**This is the proper conduct:*";
P_HTM[1993]="*Na upasampādetabbaṃ,**He should not give the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[1994]="*na nissayo dātabbo,**He should not give formal support.*";
P_HTM[1995]="*na sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo,**He should not have a novice monk attend on him.*";
P_HTM[1996]="*na bhikkhunovādakasammuti sāditabbā,**He should not accept being appointed as an instructor of the nuns.*";
P_HTM[1997]="*sammatenapi bhikkhuniyo na ovaditabbā.**Even if appointed, he should not instruct the nuns.*";
P_HTM[1998]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena parivāso dinno hoti sā āpatti na āpajjitabbā, aññā vā tādisikā, tato vā pāpiṭṭhatarā;**He should not commit the same offense as the offense for which the Sangha gave him probation, nor one that is similar or worse.*";
P_HTM[1999]="*kammaṃ na garahitabbaṃ,**He should not criticize the legal procedure.*";
P_HTM[2000]="*kammikā na garahitabbā.**He should not criticize those who did the procedure.*";
P_HTM[2001]="*Na pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposatho ṭhapetabbo,**He should not cancel the observance-day procedure of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2002]="*na pavāraṇā ṭhapetabbā,**He should not cancel the invitation of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2003]="*na savacanīyaṃ kātabbaṃ,**He should not speak to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him.*";
P_HTM[2004]="*na anuvādo paṭṭhapetabbo,**He should not make accusations against a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2005]="*na okāso kāretabbo,**He should not ask a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense.*";
P_HTM[2006]="*na codetabbo,**He should not accuse a regular monk of an offense.*";
P_HTM[2007]="*na sāretabbo,**He should not remind a regular monk of an offense.*";
P_HTM[2008]="*na bhikkhūhi sampayojetabbaṃ.**He should not associate inappropriately with other monks.*";
P_HTM[2009]="*Na, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā pakatattassa bhikkhuno purato gantabbaṃ,**He should not walk in front of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2010]="*na purato nisīditabbaṃ.**He should not sit in front of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2011]="*Yo hoti saṅghassa āsanapariyanto seyyāpariyanto vihārapariyanto so tassa padātabbo. Tena ca so sāditabbo.**He should be given the last seat, the last bed, and the last dwelling of the Sangha and should consent to that.*";
P_HTM[2012]="*Na, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā pakatattena bhikkhunā puresamaṇena vā**He should not attend on a regular monk when going to families.*";
P_HTM[2013]="*pacchāsamaṇena vā kulāni upasaṅkamitabbāni,**He should not be attended on by a regular monk when going to families.*";
P_HTM[2014]="*na āraññikaṅgaṃ samādātabbaṃ,**He should not undertake the practice of staying in the wilderness.*";
P_HTM[2015]="*na piṇḍapātikaṅgaṃ samādātabbaṃ,**He should not undertake the practice of eating only almsfood.*";
P_HTM[2016]="*na ca tappaccayā piṇḍapāto nīharāpetabbo—mā maṃ jāniṃsūti.**He should not have someone bring back almsfood for him because he doesn’t want others to know about his status.*";
P_HTM[2017]="*Pārivāsikena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā āgantukena ārocetabbaṃ,**He should inform about his status when he is newly arrived in a monastery.*";
P_HTM[2018]="*āgantukassa ārocetabbaṃ,**He should inform new arrivals of his status.*";
P_HTM[2019]="*uposathe ārocetabbaṃ,**He should inform about his status on the observance-day.*";
P_HTM[2020]="*pavāraṇāya ārocetabbaṃ.**He should inform about his status on the invitation day.*";
P_HTM[2021]="*Sace gilāno hoti, dūtenapi ārocetabbaṃ.**If he is sick, he should inform about his status by messenger.*";
P_HTM[2022]="*Na, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā abhikkhuko āvāso gantabbo, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery with monks to one without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2023]="*Na, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā abhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery with monks to a non-monastery without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2024]="*Na, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā abhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā gantabbo, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2025]="*Na, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā anāvāsā abhikkhuko āvāso gantabbo, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2026]="*Na, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā anāvāsā abhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
