P_HTM[2035]="*Na, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā anāvāsā sabhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo, yatthassu bhikkhū nānāsaṃvāsakā, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2036]="*Na, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā anāvāsā sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā gantabbo, yatthassu bhikkhū nānāsaṃvāsakā, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2037]="*Na, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā vā anāvāsā vā sabhikkhuko āvāso gantabbo, yatthassu bhikkhū nānāsaṃvāsakā, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2038]="*Na, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā vā anāvāsā vā sabhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo, yatthassu bhikkhū nānāsaṃvāsakā, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2039]="*Na, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā vā anāvāsā vā sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā gantabbo, yatthassu bhikkhū nānāsaṃvāsakā, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2040]="*Gantabbo, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā sabhikkhuko āvāso, yatthassu bhikkhū samānasaṃvāsakā, yaṃ jaññā sakkomi ajjeva gantunti.**He may go from a monastery with monks to one with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2041]="*Gantabbo, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā sabhikkhuko anāvāso, yatthassu bhikkhū samānasaṃvāsakā, yaṃ jaññā sakkomi ajjeva gantunti.**He may go from a monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2042]="*Gantabbo, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā, yatthassu bhikkhū samānasaṃvāsakā, yaṃ jaññā sakkomi ajjeva gantunti.**He may go from a monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2043]="*Gantabbo, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā anāvāsā sabhikkhuko āvāso, yatthassu bhikkhū samānasaṃvāsakā, yaṃ jaññā sakkomi ajjeva gantunti.**He may go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2044]="*Gantabbo, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā anāvāsā sabhikkhuko anāvāso, yatthassu bhikkhū samānasaṃvāsakā, yaṃ jaññā sakkomi ajjeva gantunti.**He may go from a non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2045]="*Gantabbo, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā anāvāsā sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā, yatthassu bhikkhū samānasaṃvāsakā, yaṃ jaññā sakkomi ajjeva gantunti.**He may go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2046]="*Gantabbo, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā vā anāvāsā vā sabhikkhuko āvāso, yatthassu bhikkhū samānasaṃvāsakā, yaṃ jaññā sakkomi ajjeva gantunti.**He may go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2047]="*Gantabbo, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā vā anāvāsā vā sabhikkhuko anāvāso, yatthassu bhikkhū samānasaṃvāsakā, yaṃ jaññā sakkomi ajjeva gantunti.**He may go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2048]="*Gantabbo, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā vā anāvāsā vā sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā, yatthassu bhikkhū samānasaṃvāsakā, yaṃ jaññā sakkomi ajjeva gantunti.**He may go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2049]="*Na, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā pakatattena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ ekacchanne āvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2050]="*na ekacchanne anāvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not, in a non-monastery, stay in the same room as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2051]="*na ekacchanne āvāse vā anāvāse vā vatthabbaṃ.**He should not, in a monastery or a non-monastery, stay in the same room as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2052]="*Pakatattaṃ bhikkhuṃ disvā āsanā vuṭṭhātabbaṃ.**If he sees a regular monk, he should get up from his seat.*";
P_HTM[2053]="*Pakatatto bhikkhu āsanena nimantetabbo.**He should offer a seat to a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2054]="*Na pakatattena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ ekāsane nisīditabbaṃ,**He should not do walking meditation on a higher walking path than a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2055]="*na nīce āsane nisinne ucce āsane nisīditabbaṃ,**He should not do walking meditation on a walking path when a regular monk is walking on the ground.*";
P_HTM[2056]="*na chamāyaṃ nisinne āsane nisīditabbaṃ;**He should not sit on a seat when a regular monk is sitting on the ground.*";
P_HTM[2057]="*na ekacaṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ,**He should not do walking meditation on the same walking path as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2058]="*na nīce caṅkame caṅkamante ucce caṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ,**He should not do walking meditation on a higher walking path than a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2059]="*na chamāyaṃ caṅkamante caṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ.**He should not do walking meditation on a walking path when a regular monk is walking on the ground.*";
P_HTM[2060]="*Na, bhikkhave, pārivāsikena bhikkhunā pārivāsikena vuḍḍhatarena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ …pe…**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a more senior monk on probation. …*";
P_HTM[2061]="*mūlāyapaṭikassanārahena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ …pe…**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a monk deserving to be sent back to the beginning. …*";
P_HTM[2062]="*mānattārahena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ …pe…**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a monk deserving to be given the trial period. …*";
P_HTM[2063]="*mānattacārikena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ …pe…**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a monk undertaking the trial period. …*";
P_HTM[2064]="*abbhānārahena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ ekacchanne āvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2065]="*na ekacchanne anāvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not, in a non-monastery, stay in the same room as a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2066]="*na ekacchanne āvāse vā anāvāse vā vatthabbaṃ;**He should not, in a monastery or a non-monastery, stay in the same room as a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2067]="*na ekāsane nisīditabbaṃ,**He should not sit on the same seat as a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2068]="*na nīce āsane nisinne ucce āsane nisīditabbaṃ,**He should not sit on a higher seat than a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2069]="*na chamāyaṃ nisinne āsane nisīditabbaṃ;**He should not sit on a seat when a monk deserving rehabilitation is sitting on the ground.*";
P_HTM[2070]="*na ekacaṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ,**He should not do walking meditation on the same walking path as a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2071]="*na nīce caṅkame caṅkamante ucce caṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ,**He should not do walking meditation on a higher walking path than a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2072]="*na chamāyaṃ caṅkamante caṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ.**He should not do walking meditation on a walking path when a monk deserving rehabilitation is walking on the ground.*";
P_HTM[2073]="*Pārivāsikacatuttho ce, bhikkhave, parivāsaṃ dadeyya,**If, as the fourth member of a group, he gives probation,*";
P_HTM[2074]="*mūlāya paṭikasseyya,**sends back to the beginning,*";
P_HTM[2075]="*mānattaṃ dadeyya,**or gives the trial period,*";
P_HTM[2076]="*taṃvīso abbheyya, akammaṃ, na ca karaṇīyan”ti.**or as the twentieth member of a group, he rehabilitates, it is invalid and not to be done.”*";
P_HTM[2077]="*Catunnavutipārivāsikavattaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The ninety-four kinds of proper conduct for one on probation are finished.*";
P_HTM[2078]="*Atha kho āyasmā upāli yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami.**Soon afterwards Venerable Upāli went to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[2079]="*Upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[2080]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā upāli bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[2081]="*“kati nu kho, bhante, pārivāsikassa bhikkhuno ratticchedā”ti?**“How many things are there, Venerable Sir, that stop a monk on probation from counting a particular day toward his probationary period?”*";
P_HTM[2082]="*“Tayo kho, upāli, pārivāsikassa bhikkhuno ratticchedā.**“There are three such things, Upāli:*";
P_HTM[2083]="*Sahavāso, vippavāso, anārocanā—**he stays in the same room as a regular monk; he stays apart from other monks; he doesn’t inform other monks of his status.”*";
P_HTM[2084]="*ime kho, upāli, tayo pārivāsikassa bhikkhuno ratticchedā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[2085]="*Tena kho pana samayena sāvatthiyaṃ mahābhikkhusaṅgho sannipatito hoti.**On one occasion a large sangha of monks had gathered at Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[2086]="*Na sakkonti pārivāsikā bhikkhū parivāsaṃ sodhetuṃ.**The monks on probation were not able to fulfill their probationary duties.*";
P_HTM[2087]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2088]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, parivāsaṃ nikkhipituṃ.**“I allow you to set aside the probation.*";
P_HTM[2089]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nikkhipitabbo.**And it should be done like this.*";
P_HTM[2090]="*Tena pārivāsikena bhikkhunā ekaṃ bhikkhuṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**The monk on probation should approach a monk, put his upper robe over one shoulder, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[2091]="*‘parivāsaṃ nikkhipāmī’ti.**‘I set aside the probation,’*";
P_HTM[2092]="*Nikkhitto hoti parivāso.* **";
P_HTM[2093]="*‘Vattaṃ nikkhipāmī’ti.**or ‘I set aside the proper conduct.’”*";
P_HTM[2094]="*Nikkhitto hoti parivāso”.* **";
P_HTM[2095]="*Tena kho pana samayena sāvatthiyā bhikkhū tahaṃ tahaṃ pakkamiṃsu.**Soon afterwards the monks at Sāvatthī left in various directions.*";
P_HTM[2096]="*Sakkonti pārivāsikā bhikkhū parivāsaṃ sodhetuṃ.**The monks on probation were again able to fulfill their probationary duties.*";
P_HTM[2097]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2098]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, parivāsaṃ samādiyituṃ.**“I allow you to take up the probation.*";
P_HTM[2099]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, samādiyitabbo.**And it should be done like this.*";
P_HTM[2100]="*Tena pārivāsikena bhikkhunā ekaṃ bhikkhuṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**The monk on probation should approach a monk, put his upper robe over one shoulder, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[2101]="*‘parivāsaṃ samādiyāmī’ti.**‘I take up the probation,’*";
P_HTM[2102]="*Samādinno hoti parivāso.* **";
P_HTM[2103]="*‘Vattaṃ samādiyāmī’ti.**or ‘I take up the proper conduct.’”*";
P_HTM[2104]="*Samādinno hoti parivāso”.* **";
P_HTM[2105]="*Pārivāsikavattaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The proper conduct of those on probation is finished.*";
P_HTM[2106]="*2. Mūlāyapaṭikassanārahavatta**2. The proper conduct of those deserving to be sent back to the beginning*";
P_HTM[2107]="*Tena kho pana samayena mūlāyapaṭikassanārahā bhikkhū sādiyanti pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ, añjalikammaṃ, sāmīcikammaṃ, āsanābhihāraṃ, seyyābhihāraṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ, pādakathalikaṃ, pattacīvarappaṭiggahaṇaṃ, nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ.**At this time monks deserving to be sent back to the beginning consented to regular monks bowing down to them, standing up for them, raising their joined palms to them, doing acts of respect toward them, offering them a seat, offering them a bed, offering them water for washing their feet and a foot stool, offering them a foot scraper, receiving their bowl and robe, and massaging their backs when bathing.*";
P_HTM[2108]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[2109]="*“kathañhi nāma mūlāyapaṭikassanārahā bhikkhū sādiyissanti pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ …pe… nahāne piṭṭhiparikamman”ti.**“How can monks deserving to be sent back to the beginning consent to these things?”*";
P_HTM[2110]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**The monks told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2111]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[2112]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, mūlāyapaṭikassanārahā bhikkhū sādiyanti pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ …pe… nahāne piṭṭhiparikamman”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that monks deserving to be sent back to the beginning consent to these things?”*";
P_HTM[2113]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[2114]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[2115]="*“ananucchavikaṃ …pe…**“It’s not suitable …*";
P_HTM[2116]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, mūlāyapaṭikassanārahā bhikkhū sādiyissanti pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ …pe… nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ.**How can monks deserving to be sent back to the beginning consent to these things?*";
P_HTM[2117]="*Netaṃ bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[2118]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[2119]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[2120]="*“na, bhikkhave, mūlāyapaṭikassanārahena bhikkhunā sāditabbaṃ**“A monk deserving to be sent back to the beginning should not consent to:*";
P_HTM[2121]="*pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ,**Regular monks bowing down to him;*";
P_HTM[2122]="*paccuṭṭhānaṃ,**Regular monks standing up for him;*";
P_HTM[2123]="*añjalikammaṃ,**Regular monks raising their joined palms to him;*";
P_HTM[2124]="*sāmīcikammaṃ,**Regular monks doing acts of respect toward him;*";
P_HTM[2125]="*āsanābhihāro,**Regular monks offering him a seat;*";
P_HTM[2126]="*seyyābhihāro,**Regular monks offering him a bed;*";
P_HTM[2127]="*pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ,**Regular monks offering him water for washing his feet and a foot stool;*";
P_HTM[2128]="*pādakathalikaṃ,**Regular monks offering him a foot scraper;*";
P_HTM[2129]="*pattacīvarappaṭiggahaṇaṃ,**Regular monks receiving his bowl and robe;*";
P_HTM[2130]="*nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ.**Regular monks massaging his back when he is bathing.*";
P_HTM[2131]="*Yo sādiyeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he consents to any of these, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2132]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, mūlāyapaṭikassanārahānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ mithu yathāvuḍḍhaṃ abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ …pe… nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ.**Monks deserving to be sent back to the beginning should bow down to one another according to seniority, and likewise stand up, raise their joined palms, do acts of respect, offer a seat, offer a bed, offer water for washing the feet and a foot stool, offer a foot scraper, receive bowl and robe, and massage one another’s backs according to seniority when bathing.*";
P_HTM[2133]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, mūlāyapaṭikassanārahānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pañca yathāvuḍḍhaṃ—**Monks deserving to be sent back to the beginning should do five things with regular monks according to seniority:*";
P_HTM[2134]="*uposathaṃ, pavāraṇaṃ, vassikasāṭikaṃ, oṇojanaṃ, bhattaṃ.**the observance-day procedure, the invitation procedure, sharing out of rainy-season robes, meal invitations, and meals.*";
P_HTM[2135]="*Tena hi, bhikkhave, mūlāyapaṭikassanārahānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ vattaṃ paññapessāmi yathā mūlāyapaṭikassanārahehi bhikkhūhi vattitabbaṃ.**And I will lay down the proper conduct for a monk deserving to be sent back to the beginning.*";
P_HTM[2136]="*Mūlāyapaṭikassanārahena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā sammā vattitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2137]="*Tatrāyaṃ sammāvattanā—**This is the proper conduct:*";
P_HTM[2138]="*Na upasampādetabbaṃ,**He should not give the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[2139]="*na nissayo dātabbo,**He should not give formal support.*";
P_HTM[2140]="*na sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo,**He should not have a novice monk attend on him.*";
P_HTM[2141]="*na bhikkhunovādakasammuti sāditabbā,**He should not accept being appointed as an instructor of the nuns.*";
P_HTM[2142]="*sammatenapi bhikkhuniyo na ovaditabbā.**Even if appointed, he should not instruct the nuns.*";
P_HTM[2143]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena mūlāyapaṭikassanāraho kato hoti sā āpatti na āpajjitabbā, aññā vā tādisikā, tato vā pāpiṭṭhatarā;**He should not commit the same offense as the offense for which he deserves to be sent back to the beginning by the Sangha, nor one that is similar or worse.*";
P_HTM[2144]="*kammaṃ na garahitabbaṃ,**He should not criticize the legal procedure.*";
P_HTM[2145]="*kammikā na garahitabbā.**He should not criticize those who did the procedure.*";
P_HTM[2146]="*Na pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposatho ṭhapetabbo,**He should not cancel the observance-day procedure of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2147]="*na pavāraṇā ṭhapetabbā,**He should not cancel the invitation of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2148]="*na savacanīyaṃ kātabbaṃ,**He should not speak to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him.*";
P_HTM[2149]="*na anuvādo paṭṭhapetabbo,**He should not make accusations against a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2150]="*na okāso kāretabbo,**He should not ask a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense.*";
P_HTM[2151]="*na codetabbo,**He should not accuse a regular monk of an offense.*";
P_HTM[2152]="*na sāretabbo,**He should not remind a regular monk of an offense.*";
P_HTM[2153]="*na bhikkhūhi sampayojetabbaṃ.**He should not associate inappropriately with other monks.*";
P_HTM[2154]="*Na, bhikkhave, mūlāyapaṭikassanārahena bhikkhunā pakatattassa bhikkhuno purato gantabbaṃ,**He should not walk in front of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2155]="*na purato nisīditabbaṃ.**He should not sit in front of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2156]="*Yo hoti saṅghassa āsanapariyanto seyyāpariyanto vihārapariyanto so tassa padātabbo. Tena ca so sāditabbo.**He should be given the last seat, the last bed, and the last dwelling of the Sangha and should consent to that.*";
P_HTM[2157]="*Na, bhikkhave, mūlāyapaṭikassanārahena bhikkhunā pakatattena bhikkhunā puresamaṇena vā**He should not attend on a regular monk when going to families.*";
P_HTM[2158]="*pacchāsamaṇena vā kulāni upasaṅkamitabbāni,**He should not be attended on by a regular monk when going to families.*";
P_HTM[2159]="*na āraññikaṅgaṃ samādātabbaṃ,**He should not undertake the practice of staying in the wilderness.*";
P_HTM[2160]="*na piṇḍapātikaṅgaṃ samādātabbaṃ,**He should not undertake the practice of eating only almsfood.*";
P_HTM[2161]="*na ca tappaccayā piṇḍapāto nīharāpetabbo—mā maṃ jāniṃsūti.**He should not have someone bring back almsfood for him because he doesn’t want others to know about his status.*";
P_HTM[2162]="*Na, bhikkhave, mūlāyapaṭikassanārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā abhikkhuko āvāso gantabbo, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery with monks to one without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2163]="*Na, bhikkhave, mūlāyapaṭikassanārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā abhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery with monks to a non-monastery without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2164]="*Na, bhikkhave, mūlāyapaṭikassanārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā abhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā gantabbo, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2165]="*Na, bhikkhave, mūlāyapaṭikassanārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā anāvāsā abhikkhuko āvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2166]="*abhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2167]="*abhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā gantabbo, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2168]="*Na, bhikkhave, mūlāyapaṭikassanārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā vā anāvāsā vā abhikkhuko āvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2169]="*abhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2170]="*abhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā gantabbo, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2171]="*Na, bhikkhave, mūlāyapaṭikassanārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā sabhikkhuko āvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a monastery with monks to one with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2172]="*sabhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2173]="*sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā gantabbo, yatthassu bhikkhū nānāsaṃvāsakā, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2174]="*Na, bhikkhave, mūlāyapaṭikassanārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā anāvāsā sabhikkhuko āvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2175]="*sabhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2176]="*sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā gantabbo, yatthassu bhikkhū nānāsaṃvāsakā, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2177]="*Na, bhikkhave, mūlāyapaṭikassanārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā vā anāvāsā vā sabhikkhuko āvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2178]="*sabhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2179]="*sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā gantabbo, yatthassu bhikkhū nānāsaṃvāsakā, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2180]="*Gantabbo, bhikkhave, mūlāyapaṭikassanārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā sabhikkhuko āvāso …pe…**He may go from a monastery with monks to one with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2181]="*sabhikkhuko anāvāso …pe…**He may go from a monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2182]="*sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā, yatthassu bhikkhū samānasaṃvāsakā, yaṃ jaññā sakkomi ajjeva gantunti.**He may go from a monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2183]="*Gantabbo, bhikkhave, mūlāyapaṭikassanārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā anāvāsā sabhikkhuko āvāso …pe…**He may go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2184]="*sabhikkhuko anāvāso …pe…**He may go from a non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2185]="*sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā, yatthassu bhikkhū samānasaṃvāsakā, yaṃ jaññā sakkomi ajjeva gantunti.**He may go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2186]="*Gantabbo, bhikkhave, mūlāyapaṭikassanārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā vā anāvāsā vā sabhikkhuko āvāso …pe…**He may go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2187]="*sabhikkhuko anāvāso …pe…**He may go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2188]="*sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā, yatthassu bhikkhū samānasaṃvāsakā, yaṃ jaññā sakkomi ajjeva gantunti.**He may go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2189]="*Na, bhikkhave, mūlāyapaṭikassanārahena bhikkhunā pakatattena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ ekacchanne āvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2190]="*na ekacchanne anāvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not, in a non-monastery, stay in the same room as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2191]="*na ekacchanne āvāse vā anāvāse vā vatthabbaṃ;**He should not, in a monastery or a non-monastery, stay in the same room as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2192]="*pakatattaṃ bhikkhuṃ disvā āsanā vuṭṭhātabbaṃ,**If he sees a regular monk, he should get up from his seat.*";
P_HTM[2193]="*pakatatto bhikkhu āsanena nimantetabbo;**He should offer a seat to a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2194]="*na pakatattena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ ekāsane nisīditabbaṃ;**He should not sit on the same seat as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2195]="*na nīce āsane nisinne ucce āsane nisīditabbaṃ;**He should not sit on a higher seat than a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2196]="*na chamāyaṃ nisinne āsane nisīditabbaṃ;**He should not sit on a seat when a regular monk is sitting on the ground*";
P_HTM[2197]="*na ekacaṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ,**He should not do walking meditation on the same walking path as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2198]="*na nīce caṅkame caṅkamante ucce caṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ,**He should not do walking meditation on a higher walking path than a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2199]="*na chamāyaṃ caṅkamante caṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ.**He should not do walking meditation on a walking path when a regular monk is walking on the ground.*";
P_HTM[2200]="*Na, bhikkhave, mūlāyapaṭikassanārahena bhikkhunā pārivāsikena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ …pe…**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a monk on probation. …*";
P_HTM[2201]="*mūlāyapaṭikassanārahena vuḍḍhatarena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ …pe…**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a more senior monk deserving to be sent back to the beginning. …*";
P_HTM[2202]="*mānattārahena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ …pe…**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a monk deserving to be given the trial period. …*";
P_HTM[2203]="*mānattacārikena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ …pe…**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a monk undertaking the trial period. …*";
P_HTM[2204]="*abbhānārahena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ ekacchanne āvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2205]="*na ekacchanne anāvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not, in a non-monastery, stay in the same room as a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2206]="*na ekacchanne āvāse vā anāvāse vā vatthabbaṃ;**He should not, in a monastery or a non-monastery, stay in the same room as a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2207]="*na ekāsane nisīditabbaṃ;**He should not sit on the same seat as a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2208]="*na nīce āsane nisinne ucce āsane nisīditabbaṃ,**He should not sit on a higher seat than a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2209]="*na chamāyaṃ nisinne āsane nisīditabbaṃ;**He should not sit on a seat when a monk deserving rehabilitation is sitting on the ground.*";
P_HTM[2210]="*na ekacaṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ,**He should not do walking meditation on the same walking path as a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2211]="*na nīce caṅkame caṅkamante ucce caṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ,**He should not do walking meditation on a higher walking path than a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2212]="*na chamāyaṃ caṅkamante caṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ.**He should not do walking meditation on a walking path when a monk deserving rehabilitation is walking on the ground.*";
P_HTM[2213]="*Mūlāyapaṭikassanārahacatuttho ce, bhikkhave, parivāsaṃ dadeyya,**If, as the fourth member of a group, he gives probation,*";
P_HTM[2214]="*mūlāya paṭikasseyya,**sends back to the beginning,*";
P_HTM[2215]="*mānattaṃ dadeyya,**or gives the trial period,*";
P_HTM[2216]="*taṃvīso abbheyya, akammaṃ, na ca karaṇīyan”ti.**or as the twentieth member of a group, he rehabilitates, it is invalid and not to be done.”*";
P_HTM[2217]="*Mūlāyapaṭikassanārahavattaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The proper conduct of those deserving to be sent back to the beginning is finished.*";
P_HTM[2218]="*3. Mānattārahavatta**3. The proper conduct of those deserving to be given the trial period*";
P_HTM[2219]="*Tena kho pana samayena mānattārahā bhikkhū sādiyanti pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ, añjalikammaṃ, sāmīcikammaṃ, āsanābhihāraṃ, seyyābhihāraṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ, pādakathalikaṃ, pattacīvarappaṭiggahaṇaṃ, nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ.**At this time monks deserving to be given the trial period consented to regular monks bowing down to them, standing up for them, raising their joined palms to them, doing acts of respect toward them, offering them a seat, offering them a bed, offering them water for washing their feet and a foot stool, offering them a foot scraper, receiving their bowl and robe, and massaging their backs when bathing.*";
P_HTM[2220]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[2221]="*“kathañhi nāma mānattārahā bhikkhū sādiyissanti pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ, añjalikammaṃ, sāmīcikammaṃ, āsanābhihāraṃ, seyyābhihāraṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ, pādakathalikaṃ, pattacīvarappaṭiggahaṇaṃ, nahāne piṭṭhiparikamman”ti.**“How can monks deserving to be given the trial period consent to these things?”*";
P_HTM[2222]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**The monks told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha of monks gathered and questioned them:*";
P_HTM[2223]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, mānattārahā bhikkhū sādiyanti pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ …pe… nahāne piṭṭhiparikamman”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that monks deserving to be given the trial period consent to these things?”*";
P_HTM[2224]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[2225]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[2226]="*“ananucchavikaṃ …pe…**“It’s not suitable …*";
P_HTM[2227]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, mānattārahā bhikkhū sādiyissanti pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ …pe… nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ.**How can monks deserving to be given the trial period consent to these things?*";
P_HTM[2228]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[2229]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[2230]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[2231]="*“na, bhikkhave, mānattārahena bhikkhunā sāditabbaṃ**“A monk deserving to be given the trial period should not consent to:*";
P_HTM[2232]="*pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ,**Regular monks bowing down to him;*";
P_HTM[2233]="*paccuṭṭhānaṃ**Regular monks standing up for him;*";
P_HTM[2234]="*…pe…**Regular monks raising their joined palms to him;*";
P_HTM[2235]="*nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ.**Regular monks massaging his back when he is bathing.*";
P_HTM[2236]="*Yo sādiyeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he consents to any of these, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2237]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, mānattārahānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ mithu yathāvuḍḍhaṃ abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ …pe… nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ.**Monks deserving to be given the trial period should bow down to one another according to seniority, and likewise stand up, raise their joined palms, do acts of respect, offer a seat, offer a bed, offer water for washing the feet and a foot stool, offer a foot scraper, receive bowl and robe, and massage one another’s backs according to seniority when bathing.*";
P_HTM[2238]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, mānattārahānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pañca yathāvuḍḍhaṃ—**Monks deserving to be given the trial period should do five things with regular monks according to seniority:*";
P_HTM[2239]="*uposathaṃ, pavāraṇaṃ, vassikasāṭikaṃ, oṇojanaṃ, bhattaṃ.**the observance-day procedure, the invitation procedure, sharing out of rainy-season robes, meal invitations, and meals.*";
P_HTM[2240]="*Tena hi, bhikkhave, mānattārahānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ vattaṃ paññapessāmi yathā mānattārahehi bhikkhūhi vattitabbaṃ.**And I will lay down the proper conduct for a monk deserving to be given the trial period.*";
P_HTM[2241]="*Mānattārahena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā sammā vattitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2242]="*Tatrāyaṃ sammāvattanā—**This is the proper conduct:*";
P_HTM[2243]="*Na upasampādetabbaṃ …pe…**He should not give the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[2244]="*(yathā mūlāyapaṭikassanā, tathā vitthāretabbaṃ.)**He should not give formal support.*";
P_HTM[2245]="*Na bhikkhūhi sampayojetabbaṃ.**He should not associate inappropriately with other monks.*";
P_HTM[2246]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattārahena bhikkhunā pakatattassa bhikkhuno purato gantabbaṃ,**He should not walk in front of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2247]="*na purato nisīditabbaṃ.**He should not sit in front of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2248]="*Yo hoti saṅghassa āsanapariyanto seyyāpariyanto vihārapariyanto so tassa padātabbo. Tena ca so sāditabbo.**He should be given the last seat, the last bed, and the last dwelling of the Sangha and should consent to that.*";
P_HTM[2249]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattārahena bhikkhunā pakatattena bhikkhunā puresamaṇena vā**He should not attend on a regular monk when going to families.*";
P_HTM[2250]="*pacchāsamaṇena vā kulāni upasaṅkamitabbāni,**He should not be attended on by a regular monk when going to families.*";
P_HTM[2251]="*na āraññikaṅgaṃ samādātabbaṃ,**He should not undertake the practice of staying in the wilderness.*";
P_HTM[2252]="*na piṇḍapātikaṅgaṃ samādātabbaṃ,**He should not undertake the practice of eating only almsfood.*";
P_HTM[2253]="*na ca tappaccayā piṇḍapāto nīharāpetabbo—mā maṃ jāniṃsūti.**He should not have someone bring back almsfood for him because he doesn’t want others to know about his status.*";
P_HTM[2254]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā abhikkhuko āvāso gantabbo, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery with monks to one without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2255]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā abhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery with monks to a non-monastery without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2256]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā abhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā gantabbo, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2257]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā anāvāsā abhikkhuko āvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2258]="*abhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2259]="*abhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā gantabbo, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2260]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā vā anāvāsā vā abhikkhuko āvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2261]="*abhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2262]="*abhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā gantabbo, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery without monks, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2263]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā sabhikkhuko āvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a monastery with monks to one with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2264]="*sabhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2265]="*sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā gantabbo, yatthassu bhikkhū nānāsaṃvāsakā, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2266]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā anāvāsā sabhikkhuko āvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2267]="*sabhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2268]="*sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā gantabbo, yatthassu bhikkhū nānāsaṃvāsakā, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2269]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā vā anāvāsā vā sabhikkhuko āvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2270]="*sabhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2271]="*sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā gantabbo, yatthassu bhikkhū nānāsaṃvāsakā, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a regular monk or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2272]="*Gantabbo, bhikkhave, mānattārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā sabhikkhuko āvāso …pe…**He may go from a monastery with monks to one with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2273]="*sabhikkhuko anāvāso …pe…**He may go from a monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2274]="*sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā, yatthassu bhikkhū samānasaṃvāsakā, yaṃ jaññā sakkomi ajjeva gantunti.**He may go from a monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2275]="*Gantabbo, bhikkhave, mānattārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā anāvāsā sabhikkhuko āvāso …pe…**He may go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2276]="*sabhikkhuko anāvāso …pe…**He may go from a non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2277]="*sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā, yatthassu bhikkhū samānasaṃvāsakā, yaṃ jaññā sakkomi ajjeva gantunti.**He may go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2278]="*Gantabbo, bhikkhave, mānattārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā vā anāvāsā vā sabhikkhuko āvāso …pe…**He may go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2279]="*sabhikkhuko anāvāso …pe…**He may go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2280]="*sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā, yatthassu bhikkhū samānasaṃvāsakā, yaṃ jaññā sakkomi ajjeva gantunti.**He may go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2281]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattārahena bhikkhunā pakatattena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ ekacchanne āvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2282]="*na ekacchanne anāvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not, in a non-monastery, stay in the same room as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2283]="*na ekacchanne āvāse vā anāvāse vā vatthabbaṃ.**He should not, in a monastery or a non-monastery, stay in the same room as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2284]="*Pakatattaṃ bhikkhuṃ disvā āsanā vuṭṭhātabbaṃ.**If he sees a regular monk, he should get up from his seat.*";
P_HTM[2285]="*Pakatatto bhikkhu āsanena nimantetabbo.**He should offer a seat to a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2286]="*Na pakatattena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ ekāsane nisīditabbaṃ,**He should not sit on the same seat as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2287]="*na nīce āsane nisinne ucce āsane nisīditabbaṃ,**He should not sit on a higher seat than a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2288]="*na chamāyaṃ nisinne āsane nisīditabbaṃ;**He should not sit on a seat when a regular monk is sitting on the ground.*";
P_HTM[2289]="*na ekacaṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ,**He should not do walking meditation on the same walking path as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2290]="*na nīce caṅkame caṅkamante ucce caṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ,**He should not do walking meditation on a higher walking path than a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2291]="*na chamāyaṃ caṅkamante caṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ.**He should not do walking meditation on a walking path when a regular monk is walking on the ground.*";
P_HTM[2292]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattārahena bhikkhunā pārivāsikena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ …pe…**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a monk on probation. …*";
P_HTM[2293]="*mūlāyapaṭikassanārahena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ …pe…**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a monk deserving to be sent back to the beginning. …*";
P_HTM[2294]="*mānattārahena vuḍḍhatarena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ …pe…**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a more senior monk deserving to be given the trial period. …*";
P_HTM[2295]="*mānattacārikena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ …pe…**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a monk undertaking the trial period. …*";
P_HTM[2296]="*abbhānārahena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ ekacchanne āvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2297]="*na ekacchanne anāvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not, in a non-monastery, stay in the same room as a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2298]="*na ekacchanne āvāse vā anāvāse vā vatthabbaṃ;**He should not, in a monastery or a non-monastery, stay in the same room as a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2299]="*na ekāsane nisīditabbaṃ,**He should not sit on the same seat as a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2300]="*na nīce āsane nisinne ucce āsane nisīditabbaṃ,**He should not sit on a higher seat than a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2301]="*na chamāyaṃ nisinne āsane nisīditabbaṃ;**He should not sit on a seat when a monk deserving rehabilitation is sitting on the ground.*";
P_HTM[2302]="*na ekacaṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ,**He should not do walking meditation on the same walking path as a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2303]="*na nīce caṅkame caṅkamante ucce caṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ,**He should not do walking meditation on a higher walking path than a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2304]="*na chamāyaṃ caṅkamante caṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ.**He should not do walking meditation on a walking path when a monk deserving rehabilitation is walking on the ground.*";
P_HTM[2305]="*Mānattārahacatuttho ce, bhikkhave, parivāsaṃ dadeyya,**If, as the fourth member of a group, he gives probation,*";
P_HTM[2306]="*mūlāya paṭikasseyya,**sends back to the beginning,*";
P_HTM[2307]="*mānattaṃ dadeyya,**or gives the trial period,*";
P_HTM[2308]="*taṃvīso abbheyya, akammaṃ, na ca karaṇīyan”ti.**or as the twentieth member of a group, he rehabilitates, it is invalid and not to be done.”*";
P_HTM[2309]="*Mānattārahavattaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The proper conduct of those deserving to be given the trial period is finished.*";
P_HTM[2310]="*4. Mānattacārikavatta**4. The proper conduct of those undertaking the trial period*";
P_HTM[2311]="*Tena kho pana samayena mānattacārikā bhikkhū sādiyanti pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ, añjalikammaṃ, sāmīcikammaṃ, āsanābhihāraṃ, seyyābhihāraṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ, pādakathalikaṃ, pattacīvarappaṭiggahaṇaṃ, nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ.**At this time monks undertaking the trial period consented to regular monks bowing down to them, standing up for them, raising their joined palms to them, doing acts of respect toward them, offering them a seat, offering them a bed, offering them water for washing their feet and a foot stool, offering them a foot scraper, receiving their bowl and robe, and massaging their backs when bathing.*";
P_HTM[2312]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[2313]="*“kathañhi nāma mānattacārikā bhikkhū sādiyissanti pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ …pe… nahāne piṭṭhiparikamman”ti.**“How can monks undertaking the trial period consent to these things?”*";
P_HTM[2314]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**The monks told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2315]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[2316]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, mānattacārikā bhikkhū sādiyanti pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ …pe… nahāne piṭṭhiparikamman”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that monks undertaking the trial period consent to these things?”*";
P_HTM[2317]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[2318]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[2319]="*“ananucchavikaṃ …pe…**“It’s not suitable …*";
P_HTM[2320]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, mānattacārikā bhikkhū sādiyissanti pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ …pe… nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ.**How can monks undertaking the trial period consent to these things?*";
P_HTM[2321]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[2322]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[2323]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[2324]="*“Na, bhikkhave, mānattacārikena bhikkhunā sāditabbaṃ**“A monk undertaking the trial period should not consent to:*";
P_HTM[2325]="*pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ,**Regular monks bowing down to him;*";
P_HTM[2326]="*paccuṭṭhānaṃ,**Regular monks standing up for him;*";
P_HTM[2327]="*añjalikammaṃ,**Regular monks raising their joined palms to him;*";
P_HTM[2328]="*sāmīcikammaṃ,**Regular monks doing acts of respect toward him;*";
P_HTM[2329]="*āsanābhihāro,**Regular monks offering him a seat;*";
P_HTM[2330]="*seyyābhihāro,**Regular monks offering him a bed;*";
P_HTM[2331]="*pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ,**Regular monks offering him water for washing his feet and a foot stool;*";
P_HTM[2332]="*pādakathalikaṃ,**Regular monks offering him a foot scraper;*";
P_HTM[2333]="*pattacīvarappaṭiggahaṇaṃ,**Regular monks receiving his bowl and robe;*";
P_HTM[2334]="*nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ.**Regular monks massaging his back when he is bathing.*";
P_HTM[2335]="*Yo sādiyeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he consents to any of these, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2336]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, mānattacārikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ mithu yathāvuḍḍhaṃ abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ …pe… nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ.**Monks undertaking the trial period should bow down to one another according to seniority, and likewise stand up, raise their joined palms, do acts of respect, offer a seat, offer a bed, offer water for washing the feet and a foot stool, offer a foot scraper, receive bowl and robe, and massage one another’s backs according to seniority when bathing.*";
P_HTM[2337]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, mānattacārikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pañca yathāvuḍḍhaṃ—**Monks undertaking the trial period should do five things with regular monks according to seniority:*";
P_HTM[2338]="*uposathaṃ, pavāraṇaṃ, vassikasāṭikaṃ, oṇojanaṃ, bhattaṃ.**the observance-day procedure, the invitation procedure, sharing out of rainy-season robes, meal invitations, and meals.*";
P_HTM[2339]="*Tena hi, bhikkhave, mānattacārikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ vattaṃ paññapessāmi yathā mānattacārikehi bhikkhūhi vattitabbaṃ.**And I will lay down the proper conduct for a monk undertaking the trial period.*";
P_HTM[2340]="*Mānattacārikena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā sammā vattitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2341]="*Tatrāyaṃ sammāvattanā—**This is the proper conduct:*";
P_HTM[2342]="*Na upasampādetabbaṃ,**He should not give the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[2343]="*na nissayo dātabbo,**He should not give formal support.*";
P_HTM[2344]="*na sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo,**He should not have a novice monk attend on him.*";
P_HTM[2345]="*na bhikkhunovādakasammuti sāditabbā,**He should not accept being appointed as an instructor of the nuns.*";
P_HTM[2346]="*sammatenapi bhikkhuniyo na ovaditabbā.**Even if appointed, he should not instruct the nuns.*";
P_HTM[2347]="*Yāya āpattiyā saṅghena mānattaṃ dinnaṃ hoti sā āpatti na āpajjitabbā, aññā vā tādisikā, tato vā pāpiṭṭhatarā;**He should not commit the same offense as the offense for which the Sangha gave him the trial period, nor one that is similar or worse.*";
P_HTM[2348]="*kammaṃ na garahitabbaṃ,**He should not criticize the legal procedure.*";
P_HTM[2349]="*kammikā na garahitabbā.**He should not criticize those who did the procedure.*";
P_HTM[2350]="*Na pakatattassa bhikkhuno uposatho ṭhapetabbo,**He should not cancel the observance-day procedure of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2351]="*na pavāraṇā ṭhapetabbā,**He should not cancel the invitation of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2352]="*na savacanīyaṃ kātabbaṃ,**He should not speak to a regular monk to initiate a legal process against him.*";
P_HTM[2353]="*na anuvādo paṭṭhapetabbo,**He should not make accusations against a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2354]="*na okāso kāretabbo,**He should not ask a regular monk for permission to accuse him of an offense.*";
P_HTM[2355]="*na codetabbo,**He should not accuse a regular monk of an offense.*";
P_HTM[2356]="*na sāretabbo,**He should not remind a regular monk of an offense.*";
P_HTM[2357]="*na bhikkhūhi sampayojetabbaṃ.**He should not associate inappropriately with other monks.*";
P_HTM[2358]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattacārikena bhikkhunā pakatattassa bhikkhuno purato gantabbaṃ,**He should not walk in front of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2359]="*na purato nisīditabbaṃ.**He should not sit in front of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2360]="*Yo hoti saṅghassa āsanapariyanto seyyāpariyanto vihārapariyanto so tassa padātabbo. Tena ca so sāditabbo.**He should be given the last seat, the last bed, and the last dwelling of the Sangha and should consent to that.*";
P_HTM[2361]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattacārikena bhikkhunā pakatattena bhikkhunā puresamaṇena vā**He should not attend on a regular monk when going to families.*";
P_HTM[2362]="*pacchāsamaṇena vā kulāni upasaṅkamitabbāni,**He should not be attended on by a regular monk when going to families.*";
P_HTM[2363]="*na āraññikaṅgaṃ samādātabbaṃ,**He should not undertake the practice of staying in the wilderness.*";
P_HTM[2364]="*na piṇḍapātikaṅgaṃ samādātabbaṃ,**He should not undertake the practice of eating only almsfood.*";
P_HTM[2365]="*na ca tappaccayā piṇḍapāto nīharāpetabbo—mā maṃ jāniṃsūti.**He should not have someone bring back almsfood for him because he doesn’t want others to know about his status.*";
P_HTM[2366]="*Mānattacārikena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā āgantukena ārocetabbaṃ,**He should inform about his status when he is newly arrived in a monastery.*";
P_HTM[2367]="*āgantukassa ārocetabbaṃ,**He should inform new arrivals of his status .*";
P_HTM[2368]="*uposathe ārocetabbaṃ,**He should inform about his status on the observance-day.*";
P_HTM[2369]="*pavāraṇāya ārocetabbaṃ,**He should inform about his status on the invitation day.*";
P_HTM[2370]="*devasikaṃ ārocetabbaṃ.**He should inform about his status on a daily basis.*";
P_HTM[2371]="*Sace gilāno hoti, dūtenapi ārocetabbaṃ.**If he is sick, he should inform about his status by messenger.*";
P_HTM[2372]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattacārikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā abhikkhuko āvāso gantabbo, aññatra saṅghena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery with monks to one without monks, except together with a sangha or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2373]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattacārikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā abhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo, aññatra saṅghena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery with monks to a non-monastery without monks, except together with a sangha or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2374]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattacārikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā abhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā gantabbo, aññatra saṅghena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery without monks, except together with a sangha or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2375]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattacārikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā anāvāsā abhikkhuko āvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery without monks, except together with a sangha or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2376]="*abhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery without monks, except together with a sangha or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2377]="*abhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā gantabbo, aññatra saṅghena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery without monks, except together with a sangha or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2378]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattacārikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā vā anāvāsā vā abhikkhuko āvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery without monks, except together with a sangha or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2379]="*abhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery without monks, except together with a sangha or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2380]="*abhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā gantabbo, aññatra saṅghena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery without monks, except together with a sangha or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2381]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattacārikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā sabhikkhuko āvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a monastery with monks to one with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a sangha or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2382]="*sabhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a sangha or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2383]="*sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā gantabbo, yatthassu bhikkhū nānāsaṃvāsakā, aññatra saṅghena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a sangha or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2384]="*Na bhikkhave, mānattacārikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā anāvāsā sabhikkhuko āvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a sangha or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2385]="*sabhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a sangha or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2386]="*sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā gantabbo, yatthassu bhikkhū nānāsaṃvāsakā, aññatra saṅghena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a sangha or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2387]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattacārikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā vā anāvāsā vā sabhikkhuko āvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a sangha or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2388]="*sabhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo …pe…**He should not go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a sangha or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2389]="*sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā gantabbo, yatthassu bhikkhū nānāsaṃvāsakā, aññatra saṅghena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to a different Buddhist sect, except together with a sangha or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2390]="*Gantabbo, bhikkhave mānattacārikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā sabhikkhuko āvāso …pe…**He may go from a monastery with monks to one with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2391]="*sabhikkhuko anāvāso …pe…**He may go from a monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2392]="*sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā, yatthassu bhikkhū samānasaṃvāsakā, yaṃ jaññā sakkomi ajjeva gantunti.**He may go from a monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2393]="*Gantabbo, bhikkhave, mānattacārikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā anāvāsā sabhikkhuko āvāso …pe…**He may go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2394]="*sabhikkhuko anāvāso …pe…**He may go from a non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2395]="*sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā, yatthassu bhikkhū samānasaṃvāsakā, yaṃ jaññā sakkomi ajjeva gantunti.**He may go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2396]="*Gantabbo, bhikkhave, mānattacārikena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā vā anāvāsā vā sabhikkhuko āvāso …pe…**He may go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2397]="*sabhikkhuko anāvāso …pe…**He may go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2398]="*sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā, yatthassu bhikkhū samānasaṃvāsakā, yaṃ jaññā sakkomi ajjeva gantunti.**He may go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2399]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattacārikena bhikkhunā pakatattena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ ekacchanne āvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2400]="*na ekacchanne anāvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not, in a non-monastery, stay in the same room as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2401]="*na ekacchanne āvāse vā anāvāse vā vatthabbaṃ.**He should not, in a monastery or a non-monastery, stay in the same room as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2402]="*Pakatattaṃ bhikkhuṃ disvā āsanā vuṭṭhātabbaṃ.**If he sees a regular monk, he should get up from his seat.*";
P_HTM[2403]="*Pakatatto bhikkhu āsanena nimantetabbo.**He should offer a seat to a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2404]="*Na pakatattena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ ekāsane nisīditabbaṃ,**He should not sit on the same seat as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2405]="*na nīce āsane nisinne ucce āsane nisīditabbaṃ,**He should not sit on a higher seat than a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2406]="*na chamāyaṃ nisinne āsane nisīditabbaṃ;**He should not sit on a seat when a regular monk is sitting on the ground.*";
P_HTM[2407]="*na ekacaṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ,**He should not do walking meditation on the same walking path as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2408]="*na nīce caṅkame caṅkamante ucce caṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ,**He should not do walking meditation on a higher walking path than a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2409]="*na chamāyaṃ caṅkamante caṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ.**He should not do walking meditation on a walking path when a regular monk is walking on the ground.*";
P_HTM[2410]="*Na, bhikkhave, mānattacārikena bhikkhunā pārivāsikena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ …pe…**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a monk on probation. …*";
P_HTM[2411]="*mūlāyapaṭikassanārahena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ …pe…**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a monk deserving to be sent back to the beginning. …*";
P_HTM[2412]="*mānattārahena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ …pe…**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a monk deserving to be given the trial period. …*";
P_HTM[2413]="*mānattacārikena vuḍḍhatarena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ …pe…**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a more senior monk undertaking the trial period. …*";
P_HTM[2414]="*abbhānārahena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ ekacchanne āvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2415]="*na ekacchanne anāvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not, in a non-monastery, stay in the same room as a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2416]="*na ekacchanne āvāse vā anāvāse vā vatthabbaṃ;**He should not, in a monastery or a non-monastery, stay in the same room as a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2417]="*na ekāsane nisīditabbaṃ,**He should not sit on the same seat as a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2418]="*na nīce āsane nisinne ucce āsane nisīditabbaṃ,**He should not sit on a higher seat than a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2419]="*na chamāyaṃ nisinne āsane nisīditabbaṃ;**He should not sit on a seat when a monk deserving rehabilitation is sitting on the ground.*";
P_HTM[2420]="*na ekacaṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ,**He should not do walking meditation on the same walking path as a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2421]="*na nīce caṅkame caṅkamante ucce caṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ,**He should not do walking meditation on a higher walking path than a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2422]="*na chamāyaṃ caṅkamante caṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ.**He should not do walking meditation on a walking path when a monk deserving rehabilitation is walking on the ground.*";
P_HTM[2423]="*Mānattacārikacatuttho ce, bhikkhave, parivāsaṃ dadeyya,**If, as the fourth member of a group, he gives probation,*";
P_HTM[2424]="*mūlāya paṭikasseyya,**sends back to the beginning,*";
P_HTM[2425]="*mānattaṃ dadeyya,**or gives the trial period,*";
P_HTM[2426]="*taṃvīso abbheyya, akammaṃ, na ca karaṇīyan”ti.**or as the twentieth member of a group, he rehabilitates, it is invalid and not to be done.”*";
P_HTM[2427]="*Atha kho āyasmā upāli yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Soon afterwards Venerable Upāli went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[2428]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā upāli bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[2429]="*“kati nu kho, bhante, mānattacārikassa bhikkhuno ratticchedā”ti?**“How many things are there, Venerable Sir, that stop a monk undertaking the trial period from counting a particular day toward his trial period?”*";
P_HTM[2430]="*“Cattāro kho, upāli, mānattacārikassa bhikkhuno ratticchedā.**“There are four such things, Upāli:*";
P_HTM[2431]="*Sahavāso, vippavāso, anārocanā, ūne gaṇe caraṇaṃ—**he stays in the same room as a regular monk; he stays apart from other monks; he doesn’t inform other monks of his status; he travels without a group.”*";
P_HTM[2432]="*ime kho, upāli, cattāro mānattacārikassa bhikkhuno ratticchedā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[2433]="*Tena kho pana samayena sāvatthiyaṃ mahābhikkhusaṅgho sannipatito hoti.**On one occasion a large sangha of monks had gathered at Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[2434]="*Na sakkonti mānattacārikā bhikkhū mānattaṃ sodhetuṃ.**The monks undertaking the trial period were not able to fulfill their duties.*";
P_HTM[2435]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2436]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, mānattaṃ nikkhipituṃ.**“I allow you to set aside the trial period.*";
P_HTM[2437]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nikkhipitabbaṃ.**And it should be done like this.*";
P_HTM[2438]="*Tena mānattacārikena bhikkhunā ekaṃ bhikkhuṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**The monk undertaking the trial period should approach a monk, put his upper robe over one shoulder, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[2439]="*‘mānattaṃ nikkhipāmī’ti.**‘I set aside the trial period,’*";
P_HTM[2440]="*Nikkhittaṃ hoti mānattaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2441]="*‘Vattaṃ nikkhipāmī’ti.**or ‘I set aside the proper conduct.’”*";
P_HTM[2442]="*Nikkhittaṃ hoti mānattan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[2443]="*Tena kho pana samayena sāvatthiyā bhikkhū tahaṃ tahaṃ pakkamiṃsu.**Soon afterwards the monks at Sāvatthī left in various directions.*";
P_HTM[2444]="*Sakkonti mānattacārikā bhikkhū mānattaṃ sodhetuṃ.**The monks undertaking the trial period were again able to fulfill their duties.*";
P_HTM[2445]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2446]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, mānattaṃ samādiyituṃ.**“I allow you to take up the trial period.*";
P_HTM[2447]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, samādiyitabbaṃ.**And it should be done like this.*";
P_HTM[2448]="*Tena mānattacārikena bhikkhunā ekaṃ bhikkhuṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā, evamassa vacanīyo—**The monk undertaking the trial period should approach a monk, put his upper robe over one shoulder, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[2449]="*‘mānattaṃ samādiyāmī’ti.**‘I take up the trial period,’*";
P_HTM[2450]="*Samādinnaṃ hoti mānattaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2451]="*‘Vattaṃ samādiyāmī’ti.**or ‘I take up the proper conduct.’”*";
P_HTM[2452]="*Samādinnaṃ hoti mānattan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[2453]="*Mānattacārikavattaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The proper conduct of those undertaking the trial period is finished.*";
P_HTM[2454]="*5. Abbhānārahavatta**5. The proper conduct of those deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2455]="*Tena kho pana samayena abbhānārahā bhikkhū sādiyanti pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ …pe…**At this time monks deserving rehabilitation consented to regular monks bowing down to them, standing up for them, raising their joined palms to them, doing acts of respect for them, offering them a seat, offering them a bed, offering them water for washing their feet and a foot stool, offering them a foot scraper, receiving their bowl and robe,*";
P_HTM[2456]="*nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ.**and massaging their backs when bathing.*";
P_HTM[2457]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[2458]="*“kathañhi nāma abbhānārahā bhikkhū sādiyissanti pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ …pe… nahāne piṭṭhiparikamman”ti.**“How can monks deserving rehabilitation consent to these things?”*";
P_HTM[2459]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**The monks told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2460]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[2461]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, abbhānārahā bhikkhū sādiyanti pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ …pe… nahāne piṭṭhiparikamman”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that monks deserving rehabilitation consent to these things?”*";
P_HTM[2462]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[2463]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[2464]="*“ananucchavikaṃ …pe…**“It’s not suitable …*";
P_HTM[2465]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, abbhānārahā bhikkhū sādiyissanti pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ …pe… nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ.**How can monks deserving rehabilitation consent to these things?*";
P_HTM[2466]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[2467]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[2468]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[2469]="*“na, bhikkhave, abbhānārahena bhikkhunā sāditabbaṃ**“A monk deserving rehabilitation should not consent to:*";
P_HTM[2470]="*pakatattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhivādanaṃ paccupaṭṭhānaṃ**Regular monks bowing down to him;*";
P_HTM[2471]="*…pe…**Regular monks standing up for him;*";
P_HTM[2472]="*nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ.**Regular monks massaging his back when he is bathing.*";
P_HTM[2473]="*Yo sādiyeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he consents to any of these, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2474]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, abbhānārahānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ mithu yathāvuḍḍhaṃ abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ …pe… nahāne piṭṭhiparikammaṃ.**Monks deserving rehabilitation should bow down to one another according to seniority, and likewise stand up, raise their joined palms, do acts of respect, offer a seat, offer a bed, offer water for washing the feet and a foot stool, offer a foot scraper, receive bowl and robe, and massage one another’s backs according to seniority when bathing.*";
P_HTM[2475]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, abbhānārahānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pañca yathāvuḍḍhaṃ—**Monks deserving rehabilitation should do five things with regular monks according to seniority:*";
P_HTM[2476]="*uposathaṃ, pavāraṇaṃ, vassikasāṭikaṃ, oṇojanaṃ, bhattaṃ.**the observance-day procedure, the invitation procedure, sharing out of rainy-season robes, meal invitations, and meals.*";
P_HTM[2477]="*Tena hi, bhikkhave, abbhānārahānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ vattaṃ paññapessāmi yathā abbhānārahehi bhikkhūhi vattitabbaṃ.**And I will lay down the proper conduct for a monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2478]="*Abbhānārahena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā sammā vattitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2479]="*Tatrāyaṃ sammāvattanā—**This is the proper conduct:*";
P_HTM[2480]="*Na upasampādetabbaṃ …pe…**He should not give the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[2481]="*(yathā heṭṭhā, tathā vitthāretabbaṃ)**He should not give formal support.*";
P_HTM[2482]="*na bhikkhūhi sampayojetabbaṃ.**He should not associate inappropriately with other monks.*";
P_HTM[2483]="*Na, bhikkhave, abbhānārahena bhikkhunā pakatattassa bhikkhuno purato gantabbaṃ,**He should not walk in front of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2484]="*na purato nisīditabbaṃ.**He should not sit in front of a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2485]="*Yo hoti saṅghassa āsanapariyanto seyyāpariyanto vihārapariyanto so tassa padātabbo. Tena ca so sāditabbo.**He should be given the last seat, the last bed, and the last dwelling of the Sangha and should consent to that.*";
P_HTM[2486]="*Na, bhikkhave, abbhānārahena bhikkhunā pakatattena bhikkhunā puresamaṇena vā**He should not attend on a regular monk when going to families*";
P_HTM[2487]="*pacchāsamaṇena vā kulāni upasaṅkamitabbāni;**He should not be attended on by a regular monk when going to families*";
P_HTM[2488]="*na āraññikaṅgaṃ samādātabbaṃ;**He should not undertake the practice of staying in the wilderness*";
P_HTM[2489]="*na piṇḍapātikaṅgaṃ samādātabbaṃ;**He should not undertake the practice of eating only almsfood.*";
P_HTM[2490]="*na ca tappaccayā piṇḍapāto nīharāpetabbo—mā maṃ jāniṃsūti.**He should not have someone bring back almsfood for him because he doesn’t want others to know about his status.*";
P_HTM[2491]="*Na, bhikkhave, abbhānārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā abhikkhuko āvāso gantabbo, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā.**He should not go from a monastery with monks to one without monks, except together with a sangha or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2492]="*Na, bhikkhave, abbhānārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā abhikkhuko anāvāso gantabbo, aññatra pakatattena, aññatra antarāyā …**He should not go from a monastery with monks to a non-monastery without monks, except together with a sangha or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2493]="*pe….**He should not go from a monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery without monks, except together with a sangha or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2494]="*(Yathā heṭṭhā, tathā vitthāretabbā.)**He should not go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery without monks, except together with a sangha or if there are dangers.*";
P_HTM[2495]="*Gantabbo, bhikkhave, abbhānārahena bhikkhunā sabhikkhukā āvāsā …pe…**He may go from a monastery with monks to one with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2496]="*anāvāsā …pe…**He may go from a monastery with monks to a non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2497]="*āvāsā vā anāvāsā vā sabhikkhuko āvāso …pe…**He may go from a monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2498]="*sabhikkhuko anāvāso …pe…**He may go from a non-monastery with monks to a monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2499]="*sabhikkhuko āvāso vā anāvāso vā, yatthassu bhikkhū samānasaṃvāsakā, yaṃ jaññā sakkomi ajjeva gantunti.**He may go from a monastery or non-monastery with monks to a monastery or non-monastery with monks who belong to the same Buddhist sect if he knows he will be able to arrive on the same day.*";
P_HTM[2500]="*Na, bhikkhave, abbhānārahena bhikkhunā pakatattena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ ekacchanne āvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2501]="*na ekacchanne anāvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not, in a non-monastery, stay in the same room as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2502]="*na ekacchanne āvāse vā anāvāse vā vatthabbaṃ;**He should not, in a monastery or a non-monastery, stay in the same room as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2503]="*pakatattaṃ bhikkhuṃ disvā āsanā vuṭṭhātabbaṃ,**If he sees a regular monk, he should get up from his seat.*";
P_HTM[2504]="*pakatatto bhikkhu āsanena nimantetabbo;**He should offer a seat to a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2505]="*na pakatattena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ ekāsane nisīditabbaṃ,**He should not sit on the same seat as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2506]="*na nīce āsane nisinne ucce āsane nisīditabbaṃ,**He should not sit on a higher seat than a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2507]="*na chamāyaṃ nisinne āsane nisīditabbaṃ;**He should not sit on a seat when a regular monk is sitting on the ground.*";
P_HTM[2508]="*na ekacaṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ,**He should not do walking meditation on the same walking path as a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2509]="*na nīce caṅkame caṅkamante ucce caṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ,**He should not do walking meditation on a higher walking path than a regular monk.*";
P_HTM[2510]="*na chamāyaṃ caṅkamante caṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ.**He should not do walking meditation on a walking path when a regular monk is walking on the ground.*";
P_HTM[2511]="*Na, bhikkhave, abbhānārahena bhikkhunā pārivāsikena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ …pe…**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a monk on probation. …*";
P_HTM[2512]="*mūlāyapaṭikassanārahena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ …pe…**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a monk deserving to be sent back to the beginning. …*";
P_HTM[2513]="*mānattārahena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ …pe…**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a monk deserving to be given the trial period. …*";
P_HTM[2514]="*mānattacārikena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ …pe…**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a monk undertaking the trial period. …*";
P_HTM[2515]="*abbhānārahena vuḍḍhatarena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ ekacchanne āvāse vatthabbaṃ,**He should not, in a monastery, stay in the same room as a more senior monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2516]="*na ekacchanne anāvāse vatthabbaṃ;**He should not, in a non-monastery, stay in the same room as a more senior monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2517]="*na ekacchanne āvāse vā anāvāse vā vatthabbaṃ;**He should not, in a monastery or a non-monastery, stay in the same room as a more senior monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2518]="*na ekāsane nisīditabbaṃ,**He should not sit on the same seat as a more senior monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2519]="*na nīce āsane nisinne ucce āsane nisīditabbaṃ,**He should not sit on a higher seat than a more senior monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2520]="*na chamāyaṃ nisinne āsane nisīditabbaṃ;**He should not sit on a seat when a more senior monk deserving rehabilitation is sitting on the ground.*";
P_HTM[2521]="*na ekacaṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ,**He should not do walking meditation on the same walking path as a more senior monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2522]="*na nīce caṅkame caṅkamante ucce caṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ,**He should not do walking meditation on a higher walking path than a more senior monk deserving rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2523]="*na chamāyaṃ caṅkamante caṅkame caṅkamitabbaṃ.**He should not do walking meditation on a walking path when a more senior monk deserving rehabilitation is walking on the ground.*";
P_HTM[2524]="*Abbhānārahacatuttho ce, bhikkhave, parivāsaṃ dadeyya,**If, as the fourth member of a group, he gives probation,*";
P_HTM[2525]="*mūlāya paṭikasseyya,**sends back to the beginning,*";
P_HTM[2526]="*mānattaṃ dadeyya,**or gives the trial period,*";
P_HTM[2527]="*taṃvīso abbheyya, akammaṃ, na ca karaṇīyan”ti.**or as the twentieth member of a group, he rehabilitates, it is invalid and not to be done.”*";
P_HTM[2528]="*Abbhānārahavattaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The proper conduct of those deserving rehabilitation is finished.*";
P_HTM[2529]="*Pārivāsikakkhandhako dutiyo.**The second chapter on those on probation is finished.*";
P_HTM[2530]="*Imamhi khandhake vatthū pañca.**In this chapter there are five topics.*";
P_HTM[2531]="*Tassuddānaṃ* **";
P_HTM[2532]="*Pārivāsikā sādenti,* **";
P_HTM[2533]="*pakatattāna bhikkhunaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2534]="*Abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[2535]="*añjaliñca sāmīciyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2536]="*Āsanaṃ seyyābhihāraṃ,* **";
P_HTM[2537]="*pādo pīṭhaṃ kathalikaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2538]="*Pattaṃ nahāne parikammaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[2539]="*ujjhāyanti ca pesalā.* **";
P_HTM[2540]="*Dukkaṭaṃ sādiyantassa,* **";
P_HTM[2541]="*Mithu pañca yathāvuḍḍhaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2542]="*Uposathaṃ pavāraṇaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[2543]="*Vassikoṇojabhojanaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2544]="*Sammā ca vattanā tattha,* **";
P_HTM[2545]="*pakatattassa gacchantaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2546]="*Yo ca hoti pariyanto,* **";
P_HTM[2547]="*pure pacchā tatheva ca.* **";
P_HTM[2548]="*Āraññapiṇḍanīhāro,* **";
P_HTM[2549]="*āgantuke uposathe;* **";
P_HTM[2550]="*Pavāraṇāya dūtena,* **";
P_HTM[2551]="*gantabbo ca sabhikkhuko.* **";
P_HTM[2552]="*Ekacchanne ca vuṭṭhānaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[2553]="*tatheva ca nimantaye;* **";
P_HTM[2554]="*Āsane nīce caṅkame,* **";
P_HTM[2555]="*chamāyaṃ caṅkamena ca.* **";
P_HTM[2556]="*Vuḍḍhatarena akammaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[2557]="*ratticchedā ca sodhanā;* **";
P_HTM[2558]="*Nikkhipanaṃ samādānaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[2559]="*vattaṃva pārivāsike.* **";
P_HTM[2560]="*Mūlāya mānattārahā,* **";
P_HTM[2561]="*tathā mānattacārikā;* **";
P_HTM[2562]="*Abbhānārahe nayo cāpi,* **";
P_HTM[2563]="*sambhedaṃ nayato puna.* **";
P_HTM[2564]="*Pārivāsikesu tayo,* **";
P_HTM[2565]="*catu mānattacārike;* **";
P_HTM[2566]="*Na samenti ratticchedesu,* **";
P_HTM[2567]="*mānattesu ca devasi;* **";
P_HTM[2568]="*Dve kammā sadisā sesā,* **";
P_HTM[2569]="*tayo kammā samāsamāti.* **";
P_HTM[2570]="*Pārivāsikakkhandhakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The second chapter on those on probation is finished.*";
P_HTM[2571]="*3. Samuccayakkhandhaka **3.  The chapter containing the collection of processes for the clearing of offenses entailing suspension *";
P_HTM[2572]="*1. Sukkavissaṭṭhi**1. Emission of semen*";
P_HTM[2573]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[2574]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā udāyī ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpanno hoti sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ appaṭicchannaṃ.**At that time Venerable Udāyī had committed one unconcealed offense of intentional emission of semen.*";
P_HTM[2575]="*So bhikkhūnaṃ ārocesi—**He told the monks about this,*";
P_HTM[2576]="*“ahaṃ, āvuso, ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjiṃ sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ appaṭicchannaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2577]="*Kathaṃ nu kho mayā paṭipajjitabban”ti?**adding, “What should I do now?”*";
P_HTM[2578]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2579]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho udāyissa bhikkhuno ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā appaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ detu.**“Well then, the Sangha should give the monk Udāyī the trial period of six days for one unconcealed offense of intentional emission of semen.*";
P_HTM[2580]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbaṃ—**And it should be given like this:*";
P_HTM[2581]="*1.1. Appaṭicchannamānatta**1.1 Trial periods for those with unconcealed offenses*";
P_HTM[2582]="*Tena, bhikkhave, udāyinā bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**“The monk Udāyī should approach the Sangha, put his upper robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and say:*";
P_HTM[2583]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjiṃ sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ appaṭicchannaṃ.**‘Venerables, I have committed one unconcealed offense of intentional emission of semen.*";
P_HTM[2584]="*Sohaṃ, bhante, saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā appaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ yācāmi.**I ask the Sangha for the trial period of six days for that offense.*";
P_HTM[2585]="*Ahaṃ, bhante, ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjiṃ sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ appaṭicchannaṃ.**I have committed one unconcealed offense of intentional emission of semen.*";
P_HTM[2586]="*Dutiyampi, sohaṃ, bhante, saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā appaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ yācāmi.**For the second time I ask the Sangha for the trial period of six days for that offense.*";
P_HTM[2587]="*Ahaṃ, bhante, ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjiṃ sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ appaṭicchannaṃ.**I have committed one unconcealed offense of intentional emission of semen.*";
P_HTM[2588]="*Tatiyampi sohaṃ, bhante, saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā appaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ yācāmī’ti.**For the third time I ask the Sangha for the trial period of six days for that offense.’*";
P_HTM[2589]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[2590]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[2591]="*Ayaṃ udāyī bhikkhu ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajji sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ appaṭicchannaṃ.**The monk Udāyī has committed one unconcealed offense of intentional emission of semen.*";
P_HTM[2592]="*So saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā appaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ yācati.**He is asking the Sangha for the trial period of six days for that offense.*";
P_HTM[2593]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho udāyissa bhikkhuno ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā appaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ dadeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should give him the trial period of six days for that offense.*";
P_HTM[2594]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[2595]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[2596]="*Ayaṃ udāyī bhikkhu ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajji sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ appaṭicchannaṃ.**The monk Udāyī has committed one unconcealed offense of intentional emission of semen.*";
P_HTM[2597]="*So saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā appaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ yācati.**He is asking the Sangha for the trial period of six days for that offense.*";
P_HTM[2598]="*Saṅgho udāyissa bhikkhuno ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā appaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ deti.**The Sangha gives him the trial period of six days for that offense.*";
P_HTM[2599]="*Yassāyasmato khamati udāyissa bhikkhuno ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā appaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattassa dānaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of giving him the trial period of six days for that offense should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[2600]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[2601]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—**For the second time I speak on this matter.*";
P_HTM[2602]="*suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[2603]="*Ayaṃ udāyī bhikkhu ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajji sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ appaṭicchannaṃ.**The monk Udāyī has committed one unconcealed offense of intentional emission of semen.*";
P_HTM[2604]="*So saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā appaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ yācati.**He is asking the Sangha for the trial period of six days for that offense.*";
P_HTM[2605]="*Saṅgho udāyissa bhikkhuno ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā appaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ deti.**The Sangha gives him the trial period of six days for that offense.*";
P_HTM[2606]="*Yassāyasmato khamati udāyissa bhikkhuno ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā appaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattassa dānaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of giving him the trial period of six days for that offense should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[2607]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[2608]="*Tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—**For the third time I speak on this matter.*";
P_HTM[2609]="*suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[2610]="*Ayaṃ udāyī bhikkhu ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajji sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ appaṭicchannaṃ.**The monk Udāyī has committed one unconcealed offense of intentional emission of semen.*";
P_HTM[2611]="*So saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā appaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ yācati.**He is asking the Sangha for the trial period of six days for that offense.*";
P_HTM[2612]="*Saṅgho udāyissa bhikkhuno ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā appaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ deti.**The Sangha gives him the trial period of six days for that offense.*";
P_HTM[2613]="*Yassāyasmato khamati udāyissa bhikkhuno ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā appaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattassa dānaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of giving him the trial period of six days for that offense should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[2614]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[2615]="*Dinnaṃ saṅghena udāyissa bhikkhuno ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā appaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ.**The Sangha has given the monk Udāyī the trial period of six days for one unconcealed offense of intentional emission of semen.*";
P_HTM[2616]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[2617]="*1.2. Appaṭicchannaabbhāna**1.2 Rehabilitation for those with unconcealed offenses*";
P_HTM[2618]="*So ciṇṇamānatto bhikkhūnaṃ ārocesi—**When he had completed the trial period, he told the monks,*";
P_HTM[2619]="*“ahaṃ, āvuso, ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjiṃ sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ appaṭicchannaṃ.**“I had committed one unconcealed offense of intentional emission of semen.*";
P_HTM[2620]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā appaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ yāciṃ.**I asked the Sangha for the trial period of six days for that offense.*";
P_HTM[2621]="*Tassa me saṅgho ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā appaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ adāsi.**The Sangha gave me the trial period,*";
P_HTM[2622]="*Sohaṃ ciṇṇamānatto.**and I have now completed it.*";
P_HTM[2623]="*Kathaṃ nu kho mayā paṭipajjitabban”ti?**What should I do now?”*";
P_HTM[2624]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2625]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho udāyiṃ bhikkhuṃ abbhetu.**“Well then, the Sangha should rehabilitate the monk Udāyī.*";
P_HTM[2626]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, abbhetabbo—**And it should be done like this:*";
P_HTM[2627]="*Tena, bhikkhave, udāyinā bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**The monk Udāyī should approach the Sangha, put his upper robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and say:*";
P_HTM[2628]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjiṃ sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ appaṭicchannaṃ, sohaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā appaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ yāciṃ.**‘Venerables, I had committed one unconcealed offense of intentional emission of semen. I asked the Sangha for the trial period of six days for that offense,*";
P_HTM[2629]="*Tassa me saṅgho ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā appaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ adāsi.**and the Sangha gave me the trial period.*";
P_HTM[2630]="*Sohaṃ, bhante, ciṇṇamānatto saṅghaṃ abbhānaṃ yācāmi.**I have now completed the trial period and I ask the Sangha for rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2631]="*Ahaṃ, bhante, ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjiṃ sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ appaṭicchannaṃ.**I had committed one unconcealed offense of intentional emission of semen.*";
P_HTM[2632]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā appaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ yāciṃ.**I asked the Sangha for the trial period of six days for that offense,*";
P_HTM[2633]="*Tassa me saṅgho ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā appaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ adāsi.**and the Sangha gave me the trial period.*";
P_HTM[2634]="*Sohaṃ ciṇṇamānatto dutiyampi, bhante, saṅghaṃ abbhānaṃ yācāmi.**I have now completed the trial period and for the second time I ask the Sangha for rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[2635]="*Ahaṃ, bhante, ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjiṃ sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ appaṭicchannaṃ.**I had committed one unconcealed offense of intentional emission of semen.*";
