P_HTM[3284]="*Saṅgho udāyissa bhikkhuno ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā pakkhappaṭicchannāya pakkhaparivāsaṃ adāsi.**and the Sangha gave him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3285]="*So parivasanto antarā ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajji sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ pañcāhappaṭicchannaṃ.**While he was on probation, he committed one offense of intentional emission of semen, concealed for five days.*";
P_HTM[3286]="*So saṅghaṃ antarā ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā pañcāhappaṭicchannāya mūlāyapaṭikassanaṃ yāci.**He asked the Sangha to send him back to the beginning for that offense,*";
P_HTM[3287]="*Saṅgho udāyiṃ bhikkhuṃ antarā ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā pañcāhappaṭicchannāya mūlāya paṭikassi.**which it did.*";
P_HTM[3288]="*So saṅghaṃ antarā ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā pañcāhappaṭicchannāya purimāya āpattiyā samodhānaparivāsaṃ yāci.**He then asked the Sangha to give him probation for that offense, simultaneous with the probation for the previous offense,*";
P_HTM[3289]="*Saṅgho udāyissa bhikkhuno antarā ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā pañcāhappaṭicchannāya purimāya āpattiyā samodhānaparivāsaṃ adāsi.**and the Sangha gave him that simultaneous probation.*";
P_HTM[3290]="*So parivutthaparivāso mānattāraho antarā ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajji sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ pañcāhappaṭicchannaṃ.**When he had completed the probation, while deserving the trial period of six days, he committed one offense of intentional emission of semen, concealed for five days.*";
P_HTM[3291]="*So saṅghaṃ antarā ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā pañcāhappaṭicchannāya mūlāyapaṭikassanaṃ yāci.**He asked the Sangha to send him back to the beginning for that offense,*";
P_HTM[3292]="*Saṅgho udāyiṃ bhikkhuṃ antarā ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā pañcāhappaṭicchannāya mūlāya paṭikassi.**which it did.*";
P_HTM[3293]="*So saṅghaṃ antarā ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā pañcāhappaṭicchannāya purimāya āpattiyā samodhānaparivāsaṃ yāci.**He then asked the Sangha to give him probation for that offense, simultaneous with the probation for the previous offense,*";
P_HTM[3294]="*Saṅgho udāyissa bhikkhuno antarā ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā pañcāhappaṭicchannāya purimāya āpattiyā samodhānaparivāsaṃ adāsi.**and the Sangha gave him that simultaneous probation.*";
P_HTM[3295]="*So parivutthaparivāso saṅghaṃ tissannaṃ āpattīnaṃ chārattaṃ mānattaṃ yāci.**When he had completed the probation, he asked the Sangha for the trial period of six days for the three offenses,*";
P_HTM[3296]="*Saṅgho udāyissa bhikkhuno tissannaṃ āpattīnaṃ chārattaṃ mānattaṃ adāsi.**and the Sangha gave him the trial period.*";
P_HTM[3297]="*So mānattaṃ caranto antarā ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajji sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ pañcāhappaṭicchannaṃ.**While he was undertaking the trial period, he committed one offense of intentional emission of semen, concealed for five days.*";
P_HTM[3298]="*So saṅghaṃ antarā ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā pañcāhappaṭicchannāya mūlāyapaṭikassanaṃ yāci.**He asked the Sangha to send him back to the beginning for that offense,*";
P_HTM[3299]="*Saṅgho udāyiṃ bhikkhuṃ antarā ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā pañcāhappaṭicchannāya mūlāya paṭikassi.**which it did.*";
P_HTM[3300]="*So saṅghaṃ antarā ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā pañcāhappaṭicchannāya purimāya āpattiyā samodhānaparivāsaṃ yāci.**He then asked the Sangha to give him probation for that offense, simultaneous with the probation for the previous offense,*";
P_HTM[3301]="*Saṅgho udāyissa bhikkhuno antarā ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā pañcāhappaṭicchannāya purimāya āpattiyā samodhānaparivāsaṃ adāsi.**and the Sangha gave him that simultaneous probation.*";
P_HTM[3302]="*So parivutthaparivāso saṅghaṃ antarā ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā pañcāhappaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ yāci.**He then asked the Sangha to give him the trial period of six days for that offense,*";
P_HTM[3303]="*Saṅgho udāyissa bhikkhuno antarā ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā pañcāhappaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ adāsi.**and the Sangha gave him the trial period.*";
P_HTM[3304]="*So ciṇṇamānatto abbhānāraho antarā ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajji sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ pañcāhappaṭicchannaṃ.**When he had completed the trial period, while deserving rehabilitation, he committed one offense of intentional emission of semen, concealed for five days.*";
P_HTM[3305]="*So saṅghaṃ antarā ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā pañcāhappaṭicchannāya mūlāyapaṭikassanaṃ yāci.**He asked the Sangha to send him back to the beginning for that offense,*";
P_HTM[3306]="*Saṅgho udāyiṃ bhikkhuṃ antarā ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā pañcāhappaṭicchannāya mūlāya paṭikassi.**which it did.*";
P_HTM[3307]="*So saṅghaṃ antarā ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā pañcāhappaṭicchannāya purimāya āpattiyā samodhānaparivāsaṃ yāci.**He then asked the Sangha to give him probation for that offense, simultaneous with the probation for the previous offense,*";
P_HTM[3308]="*Saṅgho udāyissa bhikkhuno antarā ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā pañcāhappaṭicchannāya purimāya āpattiyā samodhānaparivāsaṃ adāsi.**and the Sangha gave him that simultaneous probation.*";
P_HTM[3309]="*So parivutthaparivāso saṅghaṃ antarā ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā pañcāhappaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ yāci.**When he had completed the probation, he asked the Sangha to give him the trial period of six days for that offense,*";
P_HTM[3310]="*Saṅgho udāyissa bhikkhuno antarā ekissā āpattiyā sañcetanikāya sukkavissaṭṭhiyā pañcāhappaṭicchannāya chārattaṃ mānattaṃ adāsi.**and the Sangha gave him the trial period.*";
P_HTM[3311]="*So ciṇṇamānatto saṅghaṃ abbhānaṃ yācati.**He’s now completed the trial period and is asking the Sangha for rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[3312]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho udāyiṃ bhikkhuṃ abbheyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should rehabilitate him.*";
P_HTM[3313]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[3314]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[3315]="*Ayaṃ udāyī bhikkhu ekaṃ āpattiṃ āpajji sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ pakkhappaṭicchannaṃ …pe…**The monk Udāyī had committed one offense of intentional emission of semen, concealed for a half-month. …*";
P_HTM[3316]="*so ciṇṇamānatto saṅghaṃ abbhānaṃ yācati.**He’s now completed the trial period and is asking the Sangha for rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[3317]="*Saṅgho udāyiṃ bhikkhuṃ abbheti.**The Sangha rehabilitates him.*";
P_HTM[3318]="*Yassāyasmato khamati udāyissa bhikkhuno abbhānaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of rehabilitating him should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[3319]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[3320]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[3321]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe….**For the third time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[3322]="*Abbhito saṅghena udāyī bhikkhu.**The Sangha has rehabilitated the monk Udāyī.*";
P_HTM[3323]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[3324]="*Sukkavissaṭṭhi samattā.**The section on emission of semen is finished.*";
P_HTM[3325]="*2. Parivāsa**2. Probation*";
P_HTM[3326]="*2.1. Agghasamodhānaparivāsa**2.1 Simultaneous probations according to the longest duration*";
P_HTM[3327]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpanno hoti—**At one time a monk had committed a number of offenses entailing suspension:*";
P_HTM[3328]="*ekā āpatti ekāhappaṭicchannā, ekā āpatti dvīhappaṭicchannā, ekā āpatti tīhappaṭicchannā, ekā āpatti catūhappaṭicchannā, ekā āpatti pañcāhappaṭicchannā, ekā āpatti chāhappaṭicchannā, ekā āpatti sattāhappaṭicchannā, ekā āpatti aṭṭhāhappaṭicchannā, ekā āpatti navāhappaṭicchannā, ekā āpatti dasāhappaṭicchannā.**one concealed for one day, one for two days, one for three days, one for four days, one for five days, one for six days, one for seven days, one for eight days, one for nine days, and one for ten days.*";
P_HTM[3329]="*So bhikkhūnaṃ ārocesi—**He told the monks about this,*";
P_HTM[3330]="*“ahaṃ, āvuso, sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ—* **";
P_HTM[3331]="*ekā āpatti ekāhappaṭicchannā …pe…* **";
P_HTM[3332]="*ekā āpatti dasāhappaṭicchannā.* **";
P_HTM[3333]="*Kathaṃ nu kho mayā paṭipajjitabban”ti?**adding, “What should I do now?”*";
P_HTM[3334]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3335]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho tassa bhikkhuno tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ yā āpatti dasāhappaṭicchannā tassā agghena samodhānaparivāsaṃ detu.**“Well then, the Sangha should give that monk simultaneous probation according to the longest duration, that is, for the offense that was concealed for ten days.*";
P_HTM[3336]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbo—**And it should be given like this:*";
P_HTM[3337]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā …pe…**That monk should approach the Sangha, put his upper robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms,*";
P_HTM[3338]="*evamassa vacanīyo—**and say:*";
P_HTM[3339]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ—**‘Venerables, I have committed a number of offenses entailing suspension:*";
P_HTM[3340]="*ekā āpatti ekāhappaṭicchannā …pe…**one concealed for one day …*";
P_HTM[3341]="*ekā āpatti dasāhappaṭicchannā.**one for ten days.*";
P_HTM[3342]="*Sohaṃ, bhante, saṅghaṃ tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ yā āpatti dasāhappaṭicchannā tassā agghena samodhānaparivāsaṃ yācāmī’ti.**I ask the Sangha for simultaneous probation according to the longest duration, that is, for the offense that was concealed for ten days.’*";
P_HTM[3343]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbo.**And he should ask a second*";
P_HTM[3344]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbo.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[3345]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[3346]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[3347]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajji—**The monk so-and-so has committed a number of offenses entailing suspension:*";
P_HTM[3348]="*ekā āpatti ekāhappaṭicchannā …pe…**one concealed for one day …*";
P_HTM[3349]="*ekā āpatti dasāhappaṭicchannā.**one for ten days.*";
P_HTM[3350]="*So saṅghaṃ tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ yā āpatti dasāhappaṭicchannā tassā agghena samodhānaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He is asking the Sangha for simultaneous probation according to the longest duration, that is, for the offense that was concealed for ten days.*";
P_HTM[3351]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ yā āpatti dasāhappaṭicchannā tassā agghena samodhānaparivāsaṃ dadeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should give him that simultaneous probation.*";
P_HTM[3352]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[3353]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[3354]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajji—**The monk so-and-so has committed a number of offenses entailing suspension:*";
P_HTM[3355]="*ekā āpatti ekāhappaṭicchannā …pe…**one concealed for one day …*";
P_HTM[3356]="*ekā āpatti dasāhappaṭicchannā.**one for ten days.*";
P_HTM[3357]="*So saṅghaṃ tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ yā āpatti dasāhappaṭicchannā tassā agghena samodhānaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He is asking the Sangha for simultaneous probation according to the longest duration, that is, for the offense that was concealed for ten days.*";
P_HTM[3358]="*Saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ yā āpatti dasāhappaṭicchannā tassā agghena samodhānaparivāsaṃ deti.**The Sangha gives him that simultaneous probation.*";
P_HTM[3359]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ yā āpatti dasāhappaṭicchannā;**Any monk who approves of giving him*";
P_HTM[3360]="*tassā agghena samodhānaparivāsassa dānaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**that simultaneous probation should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[3361]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[3362]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[3363]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe….**For the third time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[3364]="*Dinno saṅghena itthannāmassa bhikkhuno tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ yā āpatti dasāhappaṭicchannā tassā agghena samodhānaparivāso.**The Sangha has given monk so-and-so simultaneous probation according to the longest duration, that is, for the offense that was concealed for ten days.*";
P_HTM[3365]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[3366]="*2.2. Sabbacirappaṭicchannaagghasamodhāna**2.2 Simultaneous probations according to the longest duration, that is, for all the offenses that were concealed the longest*";
P_HTM[3367]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpanno hoti—**At one time a monk had committed a number of offenses entailing suspension:*";
P_HTM[3368]="*ekā āpatti ekāhappaṭicchannā, dve āpattiyo dvīhappaṭicchannāyo, tisso āpattiyo tīhappaṭicchannāyo, catasso āpattiyo catūhappaṭicchannāyo, pañca āpattiyo pañcāhappaṭicchannāyo, cha āpattiyo chāhappaṭicchannāyo, satta āpattiyo sattāhappaṭicchannāyo, aṭṭha āpattiyo aṭṭhāhappaṭicchannāyo, nava āpattiyo navāhappaṭicchannāyo, dasa āpattiyo dasāhappaṭicchannāyo.**one concealed for one day, two for two days, three for three days, four for four days, five for five days, six for six days, seven for seven days, eight for eight days, nine for nine days, ten for ten days.*";
P_HTM[3369]="*So bhikkhūnaṃ ārocesi—**He told the monks about this,*";
P_HTM[3370]="*“ahaṃ, āvuso, sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ, ekā āpatti ekāhappaṭicchannā …pe…* **";
P_HTM[3371]="*dasa āpattiyo dasāhappaṭicchannāyo.* **";
P_HTM[3372]="*Kathaṃ nu kho mayā paṭipajjitabban”ti?**adding, “What should I do now?”*";
P_HTM[3373]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3374]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho tassa bhikkhuno tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ yā āpattiyo sabbacirappaṭicchannāyo tāsaṃ agghena samodhānaparivāsaṃ detu.**“Well then, the Sangha should give that monk simultaneous probation according to the longest duration, that is, for all the offenses that were concealed the longest.*";
P_HTM[3375]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbo—**And it should be given like this:*";
P_HTM[3376]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā …pe…**That monk should approach the Sangha, put his upper robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms,*";
P_HTM[3377]="*evamassa vacanīyo—**and say:*";
P_HTM[3378]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ, ekā āpatti ekāhappaṭicchannā …pe…**‘Venerables, I have committed a number of offenses entailing suspension: one concealed for one day …*";
P_HTM[3379]="*dasa āpattiyo dasāhappaṭicchannāyo.**ten for ten days.*";
P_HTM[3380]="*Sohaṃ, bhante, saṅghaṃ tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ yā āpattiyo sabbacirappaṭicchannāyo tāsaṃ agghena samodhānaparivāsaṃ yācāmī’ti.**I ask the Sangha for simultaneous probation according to the longest duration, that is, for all the offenses that were concealed the longest.’*";
P_HTM[3381]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbo.**And he should ask a second*";
P_HTM[3382]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbo.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[3383]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[3384]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[3385]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajji, ekā āpatti ekāhappaṭicchannā …pe…**The monk so-and-so has committed a number of offenses entailing suspension: one concealed for one day …*";
P_HTM[3386]="*dasa āpattiyo dasāhappaṭicchannāyo.**ten for ten days.*";
P_HTM[3387]="*So saṅghaṃ tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ yā āpattiyo sabbacirappaṭicchannāyo tāsaṃ agghena samodhānaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He is asking the Sangha for simultaneous probation according to the longest duration, that is, for all the offenses that were concealed the longest.*";
P_HTM[3388]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ yā āpattiyo sabbacirappaṭicchannāyo tāsaṃ agghena samodhānaparivāsaṃ dadeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should give him that simultaneous probation.*";
