P_HTM[3398]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[3399]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe….**For the third time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[3400]="*Dinno saṅghena itthannāmassa bhikkhuno tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ yā āpattiyo sabbacirappaṭicchannāyo tāsaṃ agghena samodhānaparivāso.**The Sangha has given monk so-and-so simultaneous probation according to the longest duration, that is, for all the offenses that were concealed the longest.*";
P_HTM[3401]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[3402]="*2.3. Dvemāsaparivāsa**2.3 Probation for two months*";
P_HTM[3403]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpanno hoti dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**At one time a monk had committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3404]="*Tassa etadahosi—**He thought,*";
P_HTM[3405]="*“ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**“I have committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3406]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.**Let me ask the Sangha for probation for two months for one of those offenses.”*";
P_HTM[3407]="*So saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāci.**He did,*";
P_HTM[3408]="*Tassa saṅgho ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.**and the Sangha gave him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3409]="*Tassa parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami—**While he was on probation, he was conscience-stricken.*";
P_HTM[3410]="*“ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**He considered what he had done,*";
P_HTM[3411]="*Tassa me etadahosi—* **";
P_HTM[3412]="*‘ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.* **";
P_HTM[3413]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3414]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3415]="*Tassa me saṅgho ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3416]="*Tassa me parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami—* **";
P_HTM[3417]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan’”ti.**and then thought, “Let me ask the Sangha for probation for two months for the other offense too.”*";
P_HTM[3418]="*So bhikkhūnaṃ ārocesi—**He told the monks everything that had happened,*";
P_HTM[3419]="*“ahaṃ, āvuso, dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.* **";
P_HTM[3420]="*Tassa me etadahosi—* **";
P_HTM[3421]="*‘ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.* **";
P_HTM[3422]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3423]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3424]="*Tassa me saṅgho ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3425]="*Tassa me parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami—* **";
P_HTM[3426]="*‘ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.* **";
P_HTM[3427]="*Tassa me etadahosi—* **";
P_HTM[3428]="*“ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.* **";
P_HTM[3429]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan”’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3430]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3431]="*Tassa me saṅgho ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3432]="*Tassa me parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami—* **";
P_HTM[3433]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3434]="*Kathaṃ nu kho mayā paṭipajjitabban”ti?**adding, “What should I do now?”*";
P_HTM[3435]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3436]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho tassa bhikkhuno itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ detu.**“Well then, the Sangha should give that monk probation for two months for that offense.*";
P_HTM[3437]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbo—**And it should be given like this:*";
P_HTM[3438]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā, ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā, vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā, ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā, añjaliṃ paggahetvā, evamassa vacanīyo—**That monk should approach the Sangha, put his upper robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and say:*";
P_HTM[3439]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**‘Venerables, I had committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3440]="*Tassa me etadahosi—**I thought,*";
P_HTM[3441]="*“ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**“I have committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3442]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.**Let me ask the Sangha for probation for two months for one of those offenses.”*";
P_HTM[3443]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāciṃ.**I did,*";
P_HTM[3444]="*Tassa me saṅgho ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.**and the Sangha gave me that probation.*";
P_HTM[3445]="*Tassa me parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami—**While on probation, I was conscience-stricken.*";
P_HTM[3446]="*“ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**I considered what I had done,*";
P_HTM[3447]="*Tassa me etadahosi—* **";
P_HTM[3448]="*ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.* **";
P_HTM[3449]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3450]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3451]="*Tassa me saṅgho ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3452]="*Tassa me parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami—* **";
P_HTM[3453]="*“yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.**and then thought, “Let me ask the Sangha for probation for two months for the other offense too.”*";
P_HTM[3454]="*Sohaṃ, bhante, saṅghaṃ itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yācāmī’ti.**And now I ask the Sangha for probation for two months for the other offense, concealed for two months.’*";
P_HTM[3455]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbo.**And he should ask a second*";
P_HTM[3456]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbo.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[3457]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[3458]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[3459]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajji dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**The monk so-and-so had committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3460]="*Tassa etadahosi—**He thought,*";
P_HTM[3461]="*“ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**“I have committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3462]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.**Let me ask the Sangha for probation for two months for one of those offenses.”*";
P_HTM[3463]="*So saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāci.**He did,*";
P_HTM[3464]="*Tassa saṅgho ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.**and the Sangha gave him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3465]="*Tassa parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami—**While he was on probation, he was conscience-stricken.*";
P_HTM[3466]="*“ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**He considered what he had done,*";
P_HTM[3467]="*Tassa me etadahosi—* **";
P_HTM[3468]="*ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.* **";
P_HTM[3469]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3470]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3471]="*Tassa me saṅgho ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3472]="*Tassa me parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami—* **";
P_HTM[3473]="*“yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.**and then thought, “Let me ask the Sangha for probation for two months for the other offense too.”*";
P_HTM[3474]="*So saṅghaṃ itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He is now asking the Sangha for probation for two months for that other offense.*";
P_HTM[3475]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ dadeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should give him probation for two months for that other offense.*";
P_HTM[3476]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[3477]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[3478]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajji dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**The monk so-and-so had committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3479]="*Tassa etadahosi—**He thought,*";
P_HTM[3480]="*“ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**“I have committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3481]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.**Let me ask the Sangha for probation for two months for one of those offenses.”*";
P_HTM[3482]="*So saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāci.**He did,*";
P_HTM[3483]="*Tassa saṅgho ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.**and the Sangha gave him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3484]="*Tassa parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami—**While he was on probation, he was conscience-stricken.*";
P_HTM[3485]="*“ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**He considered what he had done,*";
P_HTM[3486]="*Tassa me etadahosi—* **";
P_HTM[3487]="*ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.* **";
P_HTM[3488]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3489]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3490]="*Tassa me saṅgho ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3491]="*Tassa me parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami—* **";
P_HTM[3492]="*“yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.**and then thought, “Let me ask the Sangha for probation for two months for the other offense too.”*";
P_HTM[3493]="*So saṅghaṃ itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He is now asking the Sangha for probation for two months for that other offense.*";
P_HTM[3494]="*Saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ deti.**The Sangha gives him probation for two months for that other offense.*";
P_HTM[3495]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsassa dānaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of giving him probation for two months for that other offense should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[3496]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[3497]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[3498]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe….**For the third time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[3499]="*Dinno saṅghena itthannāmassa bhikkhuno itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāso.**The Sangha has given monk so-and-so probation for two months for the other offense, concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3500]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[3501]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā tadupādāya dve māsā parivasitabbā.**Starting right there, that monk must stay on probation for two months.*";
P_HTM[3502]="*2.4. Dvemāsāparivasitabbavidhi**2.4 Processes for staying on probation for two months*";
P_HTM[3503]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjati dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**“It may be that a monk has committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3504]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti—**He thinks,*";
P_HTM[3505]="*‘ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**‘I have committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3506]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan’ti.**Let me ask the Sangha for probation for two months for one of those offenses.’*";
P_HTM[3507]="*So saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He does,*";
P_HTM[3508]="*Tassa saṅgho ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3509]="*Tassa parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami—**While on probation, he is conscience-stricken.*";
P_HTM[3510]="*‘ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**He considers all this*";
P_HTM[3511]="*Tassa me etadahosi—* **";
P_HTM[3512]="*“ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.* **";
P_HTM[3513]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3514]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3515]="*Tassa me saṅgho ekissā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3516]="*Tassa me parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami—* **";
P_HTM[3517]="*“yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan”’ti.**and thinks, ‘Let me ask the Sangha for probation for two months for the other offense too.’*";
P_HTM[3518]="*So saṅghaṃ itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He then asks the Sangha,*";
P_HTM[3519]="*Tassa saṅgho itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him probation for two months for the other offense too.*";
P_HTM[3520]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā tadupādāya dve māsā parivasitabbā.**Starting right there, that monk must stay on probation for two months.*";
P_HTM[3521]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjati dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;**It may be that a monk has committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3522]="*ekaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, ekaṃ āpattiṃ na jānāti.**He knows about one offense, but not about the other.*";
P_HTM[3523]="*So saṅghaṃ yaṃ āpattiṃ jānāti, tassā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He asks the Sangha for probation for two months for the offense he knows about,*";
P_HTM[3524]="*Tassa saṅgho tassā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3525]="*So parivasanto itarampi āpattiṃ jānāti.**While on probation, he finds out about the other offense.*";
P_HTM[3526]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti—**He considers all this*";
P_HTM[3527]="*‘ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;* **";
P_HTM[3528]="*ekaṃ āpattiṃ jāniṃ, ekaṃ āpattiṃ na jāniṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3529]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ yaṃ āpattiṃ jāniṃ tassā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3530]="*Tassa me saṅgho tassā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3531]="*Sohaṃ parivasanto itarampi āpattiṃ jānāmi.* **";
P_HTM[3532]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan’ti.**and thinks, ‘Let me ask the Sangha for probation for two months for the other offense too.’*";
P_HTM[3533]="*So saṅghaṃ itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He then asks the Sangha,*";
P_HTM[3534]="*Tassa saṅgho itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him probation for two months for the other offense too.*";
P_HTM[3535]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā tadupādāya dve māsā parivasitabbā.**Starting right there, that monk must stay on probation for two months.*";
P_HTM[3536]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjati dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;**It may be that a monk has committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3537]="*ekaṃ āpattiṃ sarati, ekaṃ āpattiṃ nassarati.**He remembers one offense, but not the other.*";
P_HTM[3538]="*So saṅghaṃ yaṃ āpattiṃ sarati, tassā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He asks the Sangha for probation for two months for the offense he remembers,*";
P_HTM[3539]="*Tassa saṅgho tassā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3540]="*So parivasanto itarampi āpattiṃ sarati.**While on probation, he remembers the other offense.*";
P_HTM[3541]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti—**He considers all this*";
P_HTM[3542]="*‘ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;* **";
P_HTM[3543]="*ekaṃ āpattiṃ sariṃ, ekaṃ āpattiṃ nassariṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3544]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ yaṃ āpattiṃ sariṃ, tassā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3545]="*Tassa me saṅgho tassā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3546]="*Sohaṃ parivasanto itarampi āpattiṃ sarāmi.* **";
P_HTM[3547]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan’ti.**and thinks, ‘Let me ask the Sangha for probation for two months for the other offense too.’*";
P_HTM[3548]="*So saṅghaṃ itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He then asks the Sangha,*";
P_HTM[3549]="*Tassa saṅgho itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him probation for two months for the other offense too.*";
P_HTM[3550]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā tadupādāya dve māsā parivasitabbā.**Starting right there, that monk must stay on probation for two months.*";
P_HTM[3551]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjati dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;**It may be that a monk has committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3552]="*ekāya āpattiyā nibbematiko, ekāya āpattiyā vematiko.**He is sure of one offense, but unsure of the other.*";
P_HTM[3553]="*So saṅghaṃ yāya āpattiyā nibbematiko, tassā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He asks the Sangha for probation for two months for the offense he is sure of,*";
P_HTM[3554]="*Tassa saṅgho tassā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3555]="*So parivasanto itarissāpi āpattiyā nibbematiko hoti.**While on probation, he becomes sure of the other offense too.*";
P_HTM[3556]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti—**He considers all this*";
P_HTM[3557]="*‘ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;* **";
P_HTM[3558]="*ekāya āpattiyā nibbematiko, ekāya āpattiyā vematiko.* **";
P_HTM[3559]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ yāya āpattiyā nibbematiko tassā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3560]="*Tassa me saṅgho tassā āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3561]="*Sohaṃ parivasanto itarissāpi āpattiyā nibbematiko.* **";
P_HTM[3562]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan’ti.**and thinks, ‘Let me ask the Sangha for probation for two months for the other offense too.’*";
P_HTM[3563]="*So saṅghaṃ itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He then asks the Sangha,*";
P_HTM[3564]="*Tassa saṅgho itarissāpi āpattiyā dvemāsappaṭicchannāya dvemāsaparivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him probation for two months for the other offense too.*";
P_HTM[3565]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā tadupādāya dve māsā parivasitabbā.**Starting right there, that monk must stay on probation for two months.*";
P_HTM[3566]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjati dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;**“It may be that a monk has committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3567]="*ekā āpatti jānappaṭicchannā, ekā āpatti ajānappaṭicchannā.**He knows he has concealed one offense, but doesn’t know he has concealed the other.*";
P_HTM[3568]="*So saṅghaṃ tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He asks the Sangha for probation for two months for both offenses,*";
P_HTM[3569]="*Tassa saṅgho tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3570]="*Tassa parivasantassa añño bhikkhu āgacchati bahussuto āgatāgamo dhammadharo vinayadharo mātikādharo paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī lajjī kukkuccako sikkhākāmo.**While he is on probation, another monk arrives. He is learned, a master of the tradition; he is an expert on the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the summaries; he is knowledgeable and competent, has a sense of conscience, and is afraid of wrongdoing and fond of the training.*";
P_HTM[3571]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**He says,*";
P_HTM[3572]="*‘kiṃ ayaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu āpanno?**‘What has this monk committed?*";
P_HTM[3573]="*Kissāyaṃ bhikkhu parivasatī’ti?**Why is he on probation?’*";
P_HTM[3574]="*Te evaṃ vadenti—**They tell him everything,*";
P_HTM[3575]="*‘ayaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajji dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;* **";
P_HTM[3576]="*ekā āpatti jānappaṭicchannā, ekā āpatti ajānappaṭicchannā.* **";
P_HTM[3577]="*So saṅghaṃ tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yācati.* **";
P_HTM[3578]="*Tassa saṅgho tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3579]="*Tāyo ayaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu āpanno, tāsāyaṃ bhikkhu parivasatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3580]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**and he says,*";
P_HTM[3581]="*‘yāyaṃ, āvuso, āpatti jānappaṭicchannā, dhammikaṃ tassā āpattiyā parivāsadānaṃ;**‘The giving of probation for the offense he knows he has concealed is legitimate,*";
P_HTM[3582]="*dhammattā ruhati.**legal, and has effect.*";
P_HTM[3583]="*Yā ca khvāyaṃ, āvuso, āpatti ajānappaṭicchannā, adhammikaṃ tassā āpattiyā parivāsadānaṃ;**The giving of probation for the offense he doesn’t know he has concealed is illegitimate,*";
P_HTM[3584]="*adhammattā na ruhati.**illegal, and has no effect.*";
P_HTM[3585]="*Ekissā, āvuso, āpattiyā bhikkhu mānattāraho’ti.**For one offense he only deserves the trial period.’*";
P_HTM[3586]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjati dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;**It may be that a monk has committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3587]="*ekā āpatti saramānappaṭicchannā, ekā āpatti assaramānappaṭicchannā.**He remembers he has concealed one offense, but doesn’t remember he has concealed the other.*";
P_HTM[3588]="*So saṅghaṃ tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He asks the Sangha for probation for two months for both offenses,*";
P_HTM[3589]="*Tassa saṅgho tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3590]="*Tassa parivasantassa añño bhikkhu āgacchati bahussuto āgatāgamo dhammadharo vinayadharo mātikādharo paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī lajjī kukkuccako sikkhākāmo.**While he is on probation, another monk arrives. He is learned, a master of the tradition; he is an expert on the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the summaries; he is knowledgeable and competent, has sense of conscience, and is afraid of wrongdoing and fond of the training.*";
P_HTM[3591]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**He says,*";
P_HTM[3592]="*‘kiṃ ayaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu āpanno?**‘What has this monk committed?*";
P_HTM[3593]="*Kissāyaṃ bhikkhu parivasatī’ti?**Why is he on probation?’*";
P_HTM[3594]="*Te evaṃ vadenti—**They tell him everything,*";
P_HTM[3595]="*‘ayaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajji dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;* **";
P_HTM[3596]="*ekā āpatti saramānappaṭicchannā, ekā āpatti assaramānappaṭicchannā.* **";
P_HTM[3597]="*So saṅghaṃ tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāci.* **";
P_HTM[3598]="*Tassa saṅgho tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3599]="*Tāyo ayaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu āpanno;* **";
P_HTM[3600]="*tāsāyaṃ bhikkhu parivasatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3601]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**and he says,*";
P_HTM[3602]="*‘yāyaṃ, āvuso, āpatti saramānappaṭicchannā dhammikaṃ tassā āpattiyā parivāsadānaṃ;**‘The giving of probation for the offense he remembers he has concealed is legitimate,*";
P_HTM[3603]="*dhammattā ruhati.**legal, and has effect.*";
P_HTM[3604]="*Yā ca khvāyaṃ, āvuso, āpatti assaramānappaṭicchannā, adhammikaṃ tassā āpattiyā parivāsadānaṃ;**The giving of probation for the offense he doesn’t remember he has concealed is illegitimate,*";
P_HTM[3605]="*adhammattā na ruhati.**illegal, and has no effect.*";
P_HTM[3606]="*Ekissā, āvuso, āpattiyā bhikkhu mānattāraho’ti.**For one offense he only deserves the trial period.’*";
P_HTM[3607]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjati dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;**It may be that a monk has committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3608]="*ekā āpatti nibbematikappaṭicchannā, ekā āpatti vematikappaṭicchannā.**He is sure he has concealed one offense, but unsure if he has concealed the other.*";
P_HTM[3609]="*So saṅghaṃ tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He asks the Sangha for probation for two months for both offenses,*";
P_HTM[3610]="*Tassa saṅgho tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3611]="*Tassa parivasantassa añño bhikkhu āgacchati bahussuto āgatāgamo dhammadharo vinayadharo mātikādharo paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī lajjī kukkuccako sikkhākāmo.**While he is on probation, another monk arrives. He is learned, a master of the tradition; he is an expert on the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the summaries; he is knowledgeable and competent, has sense of conscience, and is afraid of wrongdoing and fond of the training.*";
P_HTM[3612]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**He says,*";
P_HTM[3613]="*‘kiṃ ayaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu āpanno?**‘What has this monk committed?*";
P_HTM[3614]="*Kissāyaṃ bhikkhu parivasatī’ti?**Why is he on probation?’*";
P_HTM[3615]="*Te evaṃ vadenti—**They tell him everything,*";
P_HTM[3616]="*‘ayaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajji dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;* **";
P_HTM[3617]="*ekā āpatti nibbematikappaṭicchannā, ekā āpatti vematikappaṭicchannā.* **";
P_HTM[3618]="*So saṅghaṃ tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāci.* **";
P_HTM[3619]="*Tassa saṅgho tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3620]="*Tāyo ayaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu āpanno;* **";
P_HTM[3621]="*tāsāyaṃ bhikkhu parivasatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3622]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**and he says,*";
P_HTM[3623]="*‘yāyaṃ, āvuso, āpatti nibbematikappaṭicchannā, dhammikaṃ tassā āpattiyā parivāsadānaṃ;**‘The giving of probation for the offense he is sure he has concealed is legitimate,*";
P_HTM[3624]="*dhammattā ruhati.**legal, and has effect.*";
P_HTM[3625]="*Yā ca khvāyaṃ, āvuso, āpatti vematikappaṭicchannā adhammikaṃ tassā āpattiyā parivāsadānaṃ;**The giving of probation for the offense he is unsure if he has concealed is illegitimate,*";
P_HTM[3626]="*adhammattā na ruhati.**illegal, and has no effect.*";
P_HTM[3627]="*Ekissā, āvuso, āpattiyā bhikkhu mānattāraho’”ti.**For one offense he only deserves the trial period.’”*";
P_HTM[3628]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpanno hoti dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**At one time a monk committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3629]="*Tassa etadahosi—**He thought,*";
P_HTM[3630]="*“ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**‘I have committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3631]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.**Let me ask the Sangha for probation for one month for those offenses.’*";
P_HTM[3632]="*So saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāci.**He did,*";
P_HTM[3633]="*Tassa saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.**and the Sangha gave him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3634]="*Tassa parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami—**While he was on probation, he was conscience-stricken.*";
P_HTM[3635]="*“ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**He considered all this,*";
P_HTM[3636]="*Tassa me etadahosi—* **";
P_HTM[3637]="*‘ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.* **";
P_HTM[3638]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3639]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3640]="*Tassa me saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3641]="*Tassa me parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami.* **";
P_HTM[3642]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.**and then thought, ‘Let me ask the Sangha for probation for an additional month for those two offenses.’*";
P_HTM[3643]="*So bhikkhūnaṃ ārocesi—**He told the monks about everything,*";
P_HTM[3644]="*“ahaṃ kho, āvuso, dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.* **";
P_HTM[3645]="*Tassa me etadahosi—* **";
P_HTM[3646]="*‘ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.* **";
P_HTM[3647]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3648]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3649]="*Tassa me saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3650]="*Tassa me parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami—* **";
P_HTM[3651]="*‘ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.* **";
P_HTM[3652]="*Tassa me etadahosi—* **";
P_HTM[3653]="*“ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.* **";
P_HTM[3654]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan”’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3655]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3656]="*Tassa me saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3657]="*Tassa me parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami—* **";
P_HTM[3658]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ yāceyyan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3659]="*Kathaṃ nu kho mayā paṭipajjitabban”ti?**adding, ‘What should I do now?’*";
P_HTM[3660]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3661]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho tassa bhikkhuno dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ detu.**“Well then, the Sangha should give that monk probation for an additional month for those two offenses concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3662]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbo—**And it should be given like this:*";
P_HTM[3663]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā …pe…**That monk should approach the Sangha, put his upper robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms,*";
P_HTM[3664]="*evamassa vacanīyo—**and say:*";
P_HTM[3665]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**‘Venerables, I had committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3666]="*Tassa me etadahosi—**I thought,*";
P_HTM[3667]="*“ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**‘I have committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3668]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.**Let me ask the Sangha for probation for one month for those offenses.’*";
P_HTM[3669]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāciṃ.**I did,*";
P_HTM[3670]="*Tassa me saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.**and the Sangha gave me that probation.*";
P_HTM[3671]="*Tassa me parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami—**While on probation, I was conscience-stricken.*";
P_HTM[3672]="*“ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**I considered all this,*";
P_HTM[3673]="*Tassa me etadahosi—* **";
P_HTM[3674]="*ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.* **";
P_HTM[3675]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3676]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3677]="*Tassa me saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3678]="*Tassa me parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami—* **";
P_HTM[3679]="*“yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.**and then thought, ‘Let me ask the Sangha for probation for an additional month for those two offenses.’*";
P_HTM[3680]="*Sohaṃ, bhante, saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ yācāmī’ti.**I now ask the Sangha for probation for an additional month for those two offenses.’*";
P_HTM[3681]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbo.**And he should ask a second*";
P_HTM[3682]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbo.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[3683]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[3684]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[3685]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajji dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**The monk so-and-so had committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3686]="*Tassa etadahosi—**He thought,*";
P_HTM[3687]="*“ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**‘I have committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3688]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.**Let me ask the Sangha for probation for one month for those offenses.’*";
P_HTM[3689]="*So saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāci.**He did,*";
P_HTM[3690]="*Tassa saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.**and the Sangha gave him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3691]="*Tassa parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami—**While he was on probation, he was conscience-stricken.*";
P_HTM[3692]="*“ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**He considered all this,*";
P_HTM[3693]="*Tassa me etadahosi—* **";
P_HTM[3694]="*ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo—* **";
P_HTM[3695]="*“yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3696]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3697]="*Tassa me saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3698]="*Tassa me parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami.* **";
P_HTM[3699]="*“Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.**and then thought, ‘Let me ask the Sangha for probation for an additional month for those two offenses.’*";
P_HTM[3700]="*So saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ yācati.**He is now asking the Sangha for probation for an additional month for those two offenses.*";
P_HTM[3701]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ dadeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should give him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3702]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[3703]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[3704]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajji dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**The monk so-and-so had committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3705]="*Tassa etadahosi—**He thought,*";
P_HTM[3706]="*“ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**I have committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3707]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.**Let me ask the Sangha for probation for one month for those offenses.’*";
P_HTM[3708]="*So saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāci.**He did,*";
P_HTM[3709]="*Tassa saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.**and the Sangha gave him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3710]="*Tassa parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami—**While he was on probation, he was conscience-stricken.*";
P_HTM[3711]="*“ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**He considered all this,*";
P_HTM[3712]="*Tassa me etadahosi—* **";
P_HTM[3713]="*ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.* **";
P_HTM[3714]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3715]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3716]="*Tassa me saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3717]="*Tassa me parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami—* **";
P_HTM[3718]="*“yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.**and then thought, ‘Let me ask the Sangha for probation for an additional month for those two offenses.’*";
P_HTM[3719]="*So saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ yācati.**He is now asking the Sangha for probation for an additional month for those two offenses.*";
P_HTM[3720]="*Saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ deti.**The Sangha gives him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3721]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsassa dānaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of giving him that probation should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[3722]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[3723]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[3724]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe….**For the third time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[3725]="*Dinno saṅghena itthannāmassa bhikkhuno dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāso.**The Sangha has given monk so-and-so probation for an additional month for those two offenses, concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3726]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[3727]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā purimaṃ upādāya dve māsā parivasitabbā.**Counting the previous month, that monk must stay on probation for two months.*";
P_HTM[3728]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjati dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**“It may be that a monk has committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3729]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti—**He thinks,*";
P_HTM[3730]="*‘ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**‘I have committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3731]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan’ti.**Let me ask the Sangha for probation for one month for those offenses.’*";
P_HTM[3732]="*So saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He does,*";
P_HTM[3733]="*Tassa saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3734]="*Tassa parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami—**While on probation, he is conscience-stricken.*";
P_HTM[3735]="*‘ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.**He considers all this*";
P_HTM[3736]="*Tassa me etadahosi—* **";
P_HTM[3737]="*“ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.* **";
P_HTM[3738]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3739]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3740]="*Tassa me saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ ekamāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3741]="*Tassa me parivasantassa lajjīdhammo okkami—* **";
P_HTM[3742]="*“Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ yāceyyan”ti.**and thinks, ‘Let me ask the Sangha for probation for an additional month for those two offenses.’*";
P_HTM[3743]="*So saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ yācati.**He then asks the Sangha,*";
P_HTM[3744]="*Tassa saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him probation for an additional month.*";
P_HTM[3745]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā purimaṃ upādāya dve māsā parivasitabbā.**Counting the previous month, that monk must stay on probation for two months.*";
P_HTM[3746]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjati dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;**It may be that a monk has committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3747]="*ekaṃ māsaṃ jānāti, ekaṃ māsaṃ na jānāti.**He knows about one month, but doesn’t know about the other.*";
P_HTM[3748]="*So saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ yaṃ māsaṃ jānāti taṃ māsaṃ parivāsaṃ yācati.**He asks the Sangha for one month probation for the month he knows about,*";
P_HTM[3749]="*Tassa saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ yaṃ māsaṃ jānāti taṃ māsaṃ parivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3750]="*So parivasanto itarampi māsaṃ jānāti.**While on probation, he finds out about the other month.*";
P_HTM[3751]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti—**He considers all of this*";
P_HTM[3752]="*‘ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;* **";
P_HTM[3753]="*ekaṃ māsaṃ jāniṃ, ekaṃ māsaṃ na jāniṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3754]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ yaṃ māsaṃ jāniṃ taṃ māsaṃ parivāsaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3755]="*Tassa me saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ yaṃ māsaṃ jāniṃ taṃ māsaṃ parivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3756]="*Sohaṃ parivasanto itarampi māsaṃ jānāmi.* **";
P_HTM[3757]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ yāceyyan’ti.**and thinks, ‘Let me ask the Sangha for probation for an additional month for those two offenses.’*";
P_HTM[3758]="*So saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ yācati.**He then asks the Sangha,*";
P_HTM[3759]="*Tassa saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him probation for an additional month.*";
P_HTM[3760]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā purimaṃ upādāya dve māsā parivasitabbā.**Counting the previous month, that monk must stay on probation for two months.*";
P_HTM[3761]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjati dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;**It may be that a monk has committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3762]="*ekaṃ māsaṃ sarati, ekaṃ māsaṃ nassarati.**He remembers one month, but not the other.*";
P_HTM[3763]="*So saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ yaṃ māsaṃ sarati taṃ māsaṃ parivāsaṃ yācati.**He asks the Sangha for one month probation for the month he remembers,*";
P_HTM[3764]="*Tassa saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ yaṃ māsaṃ sarati taṃ māsaṃ parivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3765]="*So parivasanto itarampi māsaṃ sarati.**While on probation, he remembers the other month.*";
P_HTM[3766]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti—**He considers all of this*";
P_HTM[3767]="*‘ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;* **";
P_HTM[3768]="*ekaṃ māsaṃ sariṃ, ekaṃ māsaṃ nassariṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3769]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ yaṃ māsaṃ sariṃ taṃ māsaṃ parivāsaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3770]="*Tassa me saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ yaṃ māsaṃ sariṃ taṃ māsaṃ parivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3771]="*Sohaṃ parivasanto itarampi māsaṃ sarāmi.* **";
P_HTM[3772]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ yāceyyan’ti.**and thinks, ‘Let me ask the Sangha for probation for an additional month for those two offenses.’*";
P_HTM[3773]="*So saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ yācati.**He then asks the Sangha,*";
P_HTM[3774]="*Tassa saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him probation for an additional month.*";
P_HTM[3775]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā purimaṃ upādāya dve māsā parivasitabbā.**Counting the previous month, that monk must stay on probation for two months.*";
P_HTM[3776]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjati dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;**It may be that a monk has committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3777]="*ekaṃ māsaṃ nibbematiko, ekaṃ māsaṃ vematiko.**He is sure of one month, but unsure of the other.*";
P_HTM[3778]="*So saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ yaṃ māsaṃ nibbematiko taṃ māsaṃ parivāsaṃ yācati.**He asks the Sangha for one month probation for the month he is sure of,*";
P_HTM[3779]="*Tassa saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ yaṃ māsaṃ nibbematiko taṃ māsaṃ parivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3780]="*So parivasanto itarampi māsaṃ nibbematiko hoti.**While on probation, he becomes sure of the other month.*";
P_HTM[3781]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti—**He considers all this*";
P_HTM[3782]="*‘ahaṃ kho dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;* **";
P_HTM[3783]="*ekaṃ māsaṃ nibbematiko, ekaṃ māsaṃ vematiko.* **";
P_HTM[3784]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ yaṃ māsaṃ nibbematiko taṃ māsaṃ parivāsaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3785]="*Tassa me saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchānnānaṃ yaṃ māsaṃ nibbematiko taṃ māsaṃ parivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3786]="*Sohaṃ parivasanto itarampi māsaṃ nibbematiko.* **";
P_HTM[3787]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ yāceyyan’ti.**and thinks, ‘Let me ask the Sangha for probation for an additional month for those two offenses.’*";
P_HTM[3788]="*So saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ yācati.**He then asks the Sangha,*";
P_HTM[3789]="*Tassa saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ itarampi māsaṃ parivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him probation for an additional month.*";
P_HTM[3790]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā purimaṃ upādāya dve māsā parivasitabbā.**Counting the previous month, that monk must stay on probation for two months.*";
P_HTM[3791]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjati dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;**“It may be that a monk has committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3792]="*eko māso jānappaṭicchanno, eko māso ajānappaṭicchanno.**He knows he has concealed for one month, but doesn’t know he has concealed for the other.*";
P_HTM[3793]="*So saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He asks the Sangha for probation for two months for both offenses,*";
P_HTM[3794]="*Tassa saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3795]="*Tassa parivasantassa añño bhikkhu āgacchati bahussuto āgatāgamo dhammadharo vinayadharo mātikādharo paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī lajjī kukkuccako sikkhākāmo.**While he is on probation, another monk arrives. He is learned, a master of the tradition; he is an expert on the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the summaries; he is knowledgeable and competent, has sense of conscience, and is afraid of wrongdoing and fond of the training.*";
P_HTM[3796]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**He says,*";
P_HTM[3797]="*‘kiṃ ayaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu āpanno?**‘What has this monk committed?*";
P_HTM[3798]="*Kissāyaṃ bhikkhu parivasatī’ti?**Why is he on probation?’*";
P_HTM[3799]="*Te evaṃ vadenti—**They tell him everything,*";
P_HTM[3800]="*‘ayaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajji dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo.* **";
P_HTM[3801]="*Eko māso jānappaṭicchanno, eko māso ajānappaṭicchanno.* **";
P_HTM[3802]="*So saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāci.* **";
P_HTM[3803]="*Tassa saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3804]="*Tāyo ayaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu āpanno tāsāyaṃ bhikkhu parivasatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3805]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**and he says,*";
P_HTM[3806]="*‘yvāyaṃ, āvuso, māso jānappaṭicchanno dhammikaṃ tassa māsassa parivāsadānaṃ;**‘The giving of probation for the month he knows he has concealed is legitimate,*";
P_HTM[3807]="*dhammattā ruhati.**legal, and has effect.*";
P_HTM[3808]="*Yo ca khvāyaṃ, āvuso, māso ajānappaṭicchanno adhammikaṃ tassa māsassa parivāsadānaṃ;**The giving of probation for the month he doesn’t know he has concealed is illegitimate,*";
P_HTM[3809]="*adhammattā na ruhati.**illegal, and has no effect.*";
P_HTM[3810]="*Ekassa, āvuso, māsassa bhikkhu mānattāraho’ti.**For one month he only deserves the trial period.’*";
P_HTM[3811]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjati dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;**It may be that a monk has committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3812]="*eko māso saramānappaṭicchanno, eko māso assaramānappaṭicchanno.**He remembers he has concealed for one month, but doesn’t remember he has concealed for the other.*";
P_HTM[3813]="*So saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He asks the Sangha for probation for two months for both offenses,*";
P_HTM[3814]="*Tassa saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3815]="*Tassa parivasantassa añño bhikkhu āgacchati bahussuto āgatāgamo dhammadharo vinayadharo mātikādharo paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī lajjī kukkuccako sikkhākāmo.**While he is on probation, another monk arrives. He is learned, a master of the tradition; he is an expert on the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the summaries; he is knowledgeable and competent, has sense of conscience, and is afraid of wrongdoing and fond of the training.*";
P_HTM[3816]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**He says,*";
P_HTM[3817]="*‘kiṃ ayaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu āpanno?**‘What has this monk committed?*";
P_HTM[3818]="*Kissāyaṃ bhikkhu parivasatī’ti?**Why is he on probation?’*";
P_HTM[3819]="*Te evaṃ vadenti—**They tell him everything,*";
P_HTM[3820]="*‘ayaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajji dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;* **";
P_HTM[3821]="*eko māso saramānappaṭicchanno, eko māso assaramānappaṭicchanno.* **";
P_HTM[3822]="*So saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāci.* **";
P_HTM[3823]="*Tassa saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3824]="*Tāyo ayaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu āpanno tāsāyaṃ bhikkhu parivasatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3825]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**and he says,*";
P_HTM[3826]="*‘yvāyaṃ, āvuso, māso saramānappaṭicchanno dhammikaṃ tassa māsassa parivāsadānaṃ;**‘The giving of probation for the month he remembers he has concealed is legitimate,*";
P_HTM[3827]="*dhammattā ruhati.**legal, and has effect.*";
P_HTM[3828]="*Yo ca khvāyaṃ, āvuso, māso assaramānappaṭicchanno adhammikaṃ tassa māsassa parivāsadānaṃ;**The giving of probation for the month he doesn’t remember he has concealed is illegitimate,*";
P_HTM[3829]="*adhammattā na ruhati.**illegal, and has no effect.*";
P_HTM[3830]="*Ekassa, āvuso, māsassa bhikkhu mānattāraho’ti.**For one month he only deserves the trial period.’*";
P_HTM[3831]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjati dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;**It may be that a monk has committed two offenses entailing suspension, both concealed for two months.*";
P_HTM[3832]="*eko māso nibbematikappaṭicchanno, eko māso vematikappaṭicchanno.**He is sure he has concealed for one month, but unsure if he has concealed for the other.*";
P_HTM[3833]="*So saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He asks the Sangha for probation for two months for both offenses,*";
P_HTM[3834]="*Tassa saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him that probation.*";
P_HTM[3835]="*Tassa parivasantassa añño bhikkhu āgacchati bahussuto āgatāgamo dhammadharo vinayadharo mātikādharo paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī lajjī kukkuccako sikkhākāmo.**While he is on probation, another monk arrives. He is learned, a master of the tradition; he is an expert on the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the summaries; he is knowledgeable and competent, has sense of conscience, and is afraid of wrongdoing and fond of the training.*";
P_HTM[3836]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**He says,*";
P_HTM[3837]="*‘kiṃ ayaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu āpanno?**‘What has this monk committed?*";
P_HTM[3838]="*Kissāyaṃ bhikkhu parivasatī’ti?**Why is he on probation?’*";
P_HTM[3839]="*Te evaṃ vadenti—**They tell him everything,*";
P_HTM[3840]="*‘ayaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu dve saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajji dvemāsappaṭicchannāyo;* **";
P_HTM[3841]="*eko māso nibbematikappaṭicchanno, eko māso vematikappaṭicchanno.* **";
P_HTM[3842]="*So saṅghaṃ dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ yāci.* **";
P_HTM[3843]="*Tassa saṅgho dvinnaṃ āpattīnaṃ dvemāsappaṭicchannānaṃ dvemāsaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3844]="*Tāyo ayaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu āpanno tāsāyaṃ bhikkhu parivasatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3845]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**and he says,*";
P_HTM[3846]="*‘yvāyaṃ, āvuso, māso nibbematikappaṭicchanno dhammikaṃ tassa māsassa parivāsadānaṃ;**‘The giving of probation for the month he is sure he has concealed is legitimate,*";
P_HTM[3847]="*dhammattā ruhati.**legal, and has effect.*";
P_HTM[3848]="*Yo ca khvāyaṃ, āvuso, māso vematikappaṭicchanno adhammikaṃ tassa māsassa parivāsadānaṃ;**The giving of probation for the month he is unsure if he has concealed is illegitimate,*";
P_HTM[3849]="*adhammattā na ruhati.**illegal, and has no effect.*";
P_HTM[3850]="*Ekassa, āvuso, māsassa bhikkhu mānattāraho’”ti.**For one month he only deserves the trial period.’”*";
P_HTM[3851]="*2.5. Suddhantaparivāsa**2.5 Purifying probation*";
P_HTM[3852]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpanno hoti.**At one time a monk had committed a number of offenses entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[3853]="*So āpattipariyantaṃ na jānāti;**He did not know the number of offenses*";
P_HTM[3854]="*rattipariyantaṃ na jānāti;**or the number of days;*";
P_HTM[3855]="*āpattipariyantaṃ nassarati, rattipariyantaṃ nassarati;**he did not remember the number of offenses or the number of days;*";
P_HTM[3856]="*āpattipariyante vematiko, rattipariyante vematiko.**he was unsure of the number of offenses and the number of days.*";
P_HTM[3857]="*So bhikkhūnaṃ ārocesi—**He told the monks about this,*";
P_HTM[3858]="*“ahaṃ, āvuso, sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ;* **";
P_HTM[3859]="*āpattipariyantaṃ na jānāmi, rattipariyantaṃ na jānāmi;* **";
P_HTM[3860]="*āpattipariyantaṃ nassarāmi, rattipariyantaṃ nassarāmi;* **";
P_HTM[3861]="*āpattipariyante vematiko, rattipariyante vematiko.* **";
P_HTM[3862]="*Kathaṃ nu kho mayā paṭipajjitabban”ti?**adding, “What should I do now?”*";
P_HTM[3863]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3864]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho tassa bhikkhuno tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ suddhantaparivāsaṃ detu.**“Well then, the Sangha should give that monk a purifying probation for those offenses.*";
P_HTM[3865]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbo—**And it should be given like this:*";
P_HTM[3866]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā …pe…**That monk should approach the Sangha, put his upper robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms,*";
P_HTM[3867]="*evamassa vacanīyo—**and say:*";
P_HTM[3868]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ.**‘Venerables, I have committed a number of offenses entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[3869]="*Āpattipariyantaṃ na jānāmi, rattipariyantaṃ na jānāmi;**I don’t know the number of offenses or the number of days;*";
P_HTM[3870]="*āpattipariyantaṃ nassarāmi, rattipariyantaṃ nassarāmi;**I don’t remember the number of offenses or the number of days;*";
P_HTM[3871]="*āpattipariyante vematiko, rattipariyante vematiko.**I’m unsure of the number of offenses and the number of days.*";
P_HTM[3872]="*Sohaṃ, bhante, saṅghaṃ tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ suddhantaparivāsaṃ yācāmī’ti.**I ask the Sangha for a purifying probation for those offenses.’*";
P_HTM[3873]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbo.**And he should ask a second*";
P_HTM[3874]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbo.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[3875]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[3876]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[3877]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajji.**The monk so-and-so has committed a number of offenses entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[3878]="*Āpattipariyantaṃ na jānāti, rattipariyantaṃ na jānāti;**He does not know the number of offenses or the number of days;*";
P_HTM[3879]="*āpattipariyantaṃ nassarati, rattipariyantaṃ nassarati;**he does not remember the number of offenses or the number of days;*";
P_HTM[3880]="*āpattipariyante vematiko, rattipariyante vematiko.**he is unsure of the number of offenses and the number of days.*";
P_HTM[3881]="*So saṅghaṃ tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ suddhantaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He is asking the Sangha for a purifying probation for those offenses.*";
P_HTM[3882]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ suddhantaparivāsaṃ dadeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should give him a purifying probation for those offenses.*";
P_HTM[3883]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[3884]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[3885]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajji.**The monk so-and-so has committed a number of offenses entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[3886]="*Āpattipariyantaṃ na jānāti, rattipariyantaṃ na jānāti;**He does not know the number of offenses or the number of days;*";
P_HTM[3887]="*āpattipariyantaṃ nassarati, rattipariyantaṃ nassarati;**he does not remember the number of offenses or the number of days;*";
P_HTM[3888]="*āpattipariyante vematiko, rattipariyante vematiko.**he is unsure of the number of offenses and the number of days.*";
P_HTM[3889]="*So saṅghaṃ tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ suddhantaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He is asking the Sangha for purifying probation for those offenses.*";
P_HTM[3890]="*Saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ suddhantaparivāsaṃ deti.**The Sangha gives him a purifying probation for those offenses.*";
P_HTM[3891]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ suddhantaparivāsassa dānaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of giving him a purifying probation for those offenses should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[3892]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[3893]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[3894]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe….**For the third time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[3895]="*Dinno saṅghena itthannāmassa bhikkhuno tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ suddhantaparivāso.**The Sangha has given monk so-and-so a purifying probation for those offenses.*";
P_HTM[3896]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[3897]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, suddhantaparivāso dātabbo;* **";
P_HTM[3898]="*evaṃ parivāso dātabbo.* **";
P_HTM[3899]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, suddhantaparivāso dātabbo?**“When should purifying probation be given?*";
P_HTM[3900]="*Āpattipariyantaṃ na jānāti, rattipariyantaṃ na jānāti;**Purifying probation should be given when: one doesn’t know the number of offenses, nor the number of days;*";
P_HTM[3901]="*āpattipariyantaṃ nassarati, rattipariyantaṃ nassarati;**one doesn’t remember the number of offenses, nor the number of days;*";
P_HTM[3902]="*āpattipariyante vematiko, rattipariyante vematiko—**one is unsure of the number of offenses and the number of days.*";
P_HTM[3903]="*suddhantaparivāso dātabbo.* **";
P_HTM[3904]="*Āpattipariyantaṃ jānāti, rattipariyantaṃ na jānāti;**Purifying probation should be given when: one knows the number of offenses, but not the number of days;*";
P_HTM[3905]="*āpattipariyantaṃ sarati, rattipariyantaṃ nassarati;**one remembers the number of offenses, but not the number of days;*";
P_HTM[3906]="*āpattipariyante nibbematiko, rattipariyante vematiko—**one is sure of the number of offenses, but not the number of days.*";
P_HTM[3907]="*suddhantaparivāso dātabbo.* **";
P_HTM[3908]="*Āpattipariyantaṃ ekaccaṃ jānāti, ekaccaṃ na jānāti, rattipariyantaṃ na jānāti;**Purifying probation should be given when: one knows some of the offenses but not others, and not the number of days;*";
P_HTM[3909]="*āpattipariyantaṃ ekaccaṃ sarati, ekaccaṃ nassarati, rattipariyantaṃ nassarati;**one remembers some of the offenses but not others, and not the number of days;*";
P_HTM[3910]="*āpattipariyante ekacce vematiko, ekacce nibbematiko, rattipariyante vematiko—**one is sure of some of the offenses but not others, and not the number of days.*";
P_HTM[3911]="*suddhantaparivāso dātabbo.* **";
P_HTM[3912]="*Āpattipariyantaṃ na jānāti, rattipariyantaṃ ekaccaṃ jānāti, ekaccaṃ na jānāti;**“Purifying probation should be given when: one doesn’t know the number of offenses, but one knows some of the days but not others;*";
P_HTM[3913]="*āpattipariyantaṃ nassarati, rattipariyantaṃ ekaccaṃ sarati, ekaccaṃ nassarati;**one doesn’t remember the number of offenses, but one remembers some of the days but not others;*";
P_HTM[3914]="*āpattipariyante vematiko, rattipariyante ekacce vematiko, ekacce nibbematiko—**one is unsure of the number of offenses, but one is sure of some of the days but not others.*";
P_HTM[3915]="*suddhantaparivāso dātabbo.* **";
P_HTM[3916]="*Āpattipariyantaṃ jānāti, rattipariyantaṃ ekaccaṃ jānāti, ekaccaṃ na jānāti;**Purifying probation should be given when: one knows the number of offenses, and one knows some of the days but not others;*";
P_HTM[3917]="*āpattipariyantaṃ sarati, rattipariyantaṃ ekaccaṃ sarati, ekaccaṃ nassarati;**one remembers the number of offenses, and one remembers some of the days but not others;*";
P_HTM[3918]="*āpattipariyante nibbematiko, rattipariyante ekacce vematiko, ekacce nibbematiko—**one is sure of the number of offenses, and one is sure of some of the days but not others.*";
P_HTM[3919]="*suddhantaparivāso dātabbo.* **";
P_HTM[3920]="*Āpattipariyantaṃ ekaccaṃ jānāti, ekaccaṃ na jānāti;**Purifying probation should be given when: one knows some of the offenses but not others,*";
P_HTM[3921]="*rattipariyantaṃ ekaccaṃ jānāti, ekaccaṃ na jānāti;**and one knows some of the days but not others;*";
P_HTM[3922]="*āpattipariyantaṃ ekaccaṃ sarati, ekaccaṃ nassarati;**one remembers some of the offenses but not others,*";
P_HTM[3923]="*rattipariyantaṃ ekaccaṃ sarati, ekaccaṃ nassarati;**and one remembers some of the days but not others;*";
P_HTM[3924]="*āpattipariyante ekacce vematiko, ekacce nibbematiko;**one is sure of some of the offenses but not others,*";
P_HTM[3925]="*rattipariyante ekacce vematiko, ekacce nibbematiko—**and one is sure of some of the days but not others.*";
P_HTM[3926]="*suddhantaparivāso dātabbo.* **";
P_HTM[3927]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, suddhantaparivāso dātabbo.* **";
P_HTM[3928]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, parivāso dātabbo?**“When should probation be given?*";
P_HTM[3929]="*Āpattipariyantaṃ jānāti, rattipariyantaṃ jānāti;**Probation should be given when: one knows the number of offenses and the number of days;*";
P_HTM[3930]="*āpattipariyantaṃ sarati, rattipariyantaṃ sarati;**one remembers the number of offenses and the number of days;*";
P_HTM[3931]="*āpattipariyante nibbematiko, rattipariyante nibbematiko—**one is sure of the number of offenses and the number of days.*";
P_HTM[3932]="*parivāso dātabbo.* **";
P_HTM[3933]="*Āpattipariyantaṃ na jānāti, rattipariyantaṃ jānāti;**Probation should be given when: one doesn’t know the number of offenses, but one knows the number of days;*";
P_HTM[3934]="*āpattipariyantaṃ nassarati, rattipariyantaṃ sarati,**one doesn’t remember the number of offenses, but one remembers the number of days;*";
P_HTM[3935]="*āpattipariyante vematiko, rattipariyante nibbematiko—**one is unsure of the number of offenses, but sure of the number of days.*";
P_HTM[3936]="*parivāso dātabbo.* **";
P_HTM[3937]="*Āpattipariyantaṃ ekaccaṃ jānāti, ekaccaṃ na jānāti, rattipariyantaṃ jānāti;**Probation should be given when: one knows some of the offenses but not others, and one knows the number of days;*";
P_HTM[3938]="*āpattipariyantaṃ ekaccaṃ sarati, ekaccaṃ nassarati, rattipariyantaṃ sarati;**one remembers some of the offenses but not others, and one remembers the number of days;*";
P_HTM[3939]="*āpattipariyante ekacce vematiko, ekacce nibbematiko, rattipariyante nibbematiko—**one is sure of some of the offenses but not others, and sure of the number of days.”*";
P_HTM[3940]="*parivāso dātabbo.* **";
P_HTM[3941]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, parivāso dātabbo”.* **";
P_HTM[3942]="*Parivāso niṭṭhito.**The section of probation is finished.*";
P_HTM[3943]="*3. Cattālīsaka**3. The group of forty*";
P_HTM[3944]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu parivasanto vibbhami.**At one time a monk on probation disrobed.*";
P_HTM[3945]="*So puna paccāgantvā bhikkhū upasampadaṃ yāci.**He then came back and asked the monks for full ordination.*";
P_HTM[3946]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3947]="*“Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu parivasanto vibbhamati.**“It may be that a monk on probation disrobes.*";
P_HTM[3948]="*Vibbhantakassa, bhikkhave, parivāso na ruhati.**For one who has disrobed, the probation is suspended.*";
P_HTM[3949]="*So ce puna upasampajjati, tassa tadeva purimaṃ parivāsadānaṃ.**If he is given the full ordination again, he continues the previous probationary process right away.*";
P_HTM[3950]="*Yo parivāso dinno sudinno, yo parivuttho suparivuttho, avaseso parivasitabbo.**The probation that was given is valid. The probation he’s already undertaken is valid. The remainder is to be undertaken.*";
P_HTM[3951]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu parivasanto sāmaṇero hoti.**It may be that a monk on probation becomes a novice monk.*";
P_HTM[3952]="*Sāmaṇerassa, bhikkhave, parivāso na ruhati.**For a novice monk, the probation is suspended.*";
P_HTM[3953]="*So ce puna upasampajjati, tassa tadeva purimaṃ parivāsadānaṃ.**If he is given the full ordination again, he continues the previous probationary process right away.*";
P_HTM[3954]="*Yo parivāso dinno sudinno, yo parivuttho suparivuttho, avaseso parivasitabbo.**The probation that was given is valid. The probation he’s already undertaken is valid. The remainder is to be undertaken.*";
P_HTM[3955]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu parivasanto ummattako hoti.**It may be that a monk on probation goes insane.*";
P_HTM[3956]="*Ummattakassa, bhikkhave, parivāso na ruhati.**For one who is insane, the probation is suspended.*";
P_HTM[3957]="*So ce puna anummattako hoti, tassa tadeva purimaṃ parivāsadānaṃ.**If he regains his sanity, he continues the previous probationary process right away.*";
P_HTM[3958]="*Yo parivāso dinno sudinno, yo parivuttho suparivuttho, avaseso parivasitabbo.**The probation that was given is valid. The probation he’s already undertaken is valid. The remainder is to be undertaken.*";
P_HTM[3959]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu parivasanto khittacitto hoti.**It may be that a monk on probation becomes deranged.*";
P_HTM[3960]="*Khittacittassa, bhikkhave, parivāso na ruhati.**For one who is deranged, the probation is suspended.*";
P_HTM[3961]="*So ce puna akhittacitto hoti, tassa tadeva purimaṃ parivāsadānaṃ.**If he regains his sanity, he continues the previous probationary process right away.*";
P_HTM[3962]="*Yo parivāso dinno sudinno, yo parivuttho suparivuttho, avaseso parivasitabbo.**The probation that was given is valid. The probation he’s already undertaken is valid. The remainder is to be undertaken.*";
P_HTM[3963]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu parivasanto vedanāṭṭo hoti.**It may be that a monk on probation is overwhelmed by pain.*";
