P_HTM[4078]="*5. Mānattasata**5. The group of one hundred on the trial period of six days*";
P_HTM[4079]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjitvā appaṭicchādetvā vibbhamati.**“It may be that a monk commits a number of unconcealed offenses entailing suspension and then disrobes.*";
P_HTM[4080]="*So puna upasampanno tā āpattiyo nacchādeti.**Being re-ordained, he doesn’t conceal those offenses.*";
P_HTM[4081]="*Tassa, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno mānattaṃ dātabbaṃ.**That monk should be given the trial period of six days.*";
P_HTM[4082]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjitvā appaṭicchādetvā vibbhamati.**It may be that a monk commits a number of unconcealed offenses entailing suspension and then disrobes.*";
P_HTM[4083]="*So puna upasampanno tā āpattiyo chādeti.**Being re-ordained, he conceals those offenses.*";
P_HTM[4084]="*Tassa, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno pacchimasmiṃ āpattikkhandhe yathāpaṭicchanne parivāsaṃ datvā mānattaṃ dātabbaṃ.**That monk should be given probation according to the length of the subsequent concealment of that class of offenses, and he should then be given the trial period of six days.*";
P_HTM[4085]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjitvā paṭicchādetvā vibbhamati.**It may be that a monk commits a number of concealed offenses entailing suspension and then disrobes.*";
P_HTM[4086]="*So puna upasampanno tā āpattiyo nacchādeti.**Being re-ordained, he doesn’t conceal those offenses.*";
P_HTM[4087]="*Tassa, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno purimasmiṃ āpattikkhandhe yathāpaṭicchanne parivāsaṃ datvā mānattaṃ dātabbaṃ.**That monk should be given probation according to the length of the earlier concealment of that class of offenses, and he should then be given the trial period of six days.*";
P_HTM[4088]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjitvā paṭicchādetvā vibbhamati.**It may be that a monk commits a number of concealed offenses entailing suspension and then disrobes.*";
P_HTM[4089]="*So puna upasampanno tā āpattiyo chādeti.**Being re-ordained, he conceals those offenses.*";
P_HTM[4090]="*Tassa, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno purimasmiñca pacchimasmiñca āpattikkhandhe yathāpaṭicchanne parivāsaṃ datvā mānattaṃ dātabbaṃ.**That monk should be given probation according to the length of the earlier and subsequent concealment of that class of offenses, and he should then be given the trial period of six days.*";
P_HTM[4091]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjati.**“It may be that a monk commits a number of offenses entailing suspension,*";
P_HTM[4092]="*Tassa honti āpattiyo paṭicchannāyopi appaṭicchannāyopi.**both concealed and unconcealed,*";
P_HTM[4093]="*So vibbhamitvā puna upasampanno yā āpattiyo pubbe chādesi tā āpattiyo pacchā nacchādeti;**and then disrobes. Being re-ordained, he doesn’t conceal any of those offenses.*";
