P_HTM[4411]="*8. Dvebhikkhuvāraekādasaka**8. The group of eleven sections on two monks*";
P_HTM[4412]="*Dve bhikkhū saṅghādisesaṃ āpannā honti.**Two monks have each committed an offense entailing suspension,*";
P_HTM[4413]="*Te saṅghādisese saṅghādisesadiṭṭhino honti.**and they regard it as an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[4414]="*Eko chādeti, eko nacchādeti.**One conceals his offense, but not the other.*";
P_HTM[4415]="*Yo chādeti so dukkaṭaṃ desāpetabbo.**The one who conceals it is to confess an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4416]="*Yathāpaṭicchanne cassa parivāsaṃ datvā ubhinnampi mānattaṃ dātabbaṃ.**He should be given probation according to the length of the concealment of that offense, and both should then be given the trial period of six days.*";
