P_HTM[4592]="*So parivasanto antarā sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjati parimāṇāyo appaṭicchannāyo.**While on probation, he commits a number of offenses entailing suspension—specified and unconcealed.*";
P_HTM[4593]="*So saṅghaṃ antarāāpattīnaṃ mūlāyapaṭikassanaṃ yācati.**He asks the Sangha to send him back to the beginning for those offenses,*";
P_HTM[4594]="*Taṃ saṅgho antarāāpattīnaṃ mūlāya paṭikassati adhammikena kammena kuppena aṭṭhānārahena, adhammena samodhānaparivāsaṃ deti.**and it does. But the legal procedure is illegitimate, reversible, and unfit to stand. And the Sangha gives him simultaneous probation illegitimately.*";
P_HTM[4595]="*So parivasāmīti maññamāno antarā sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjati parimāṇāyo appaṭicchannāyo.**Thinking that he is on probation, he commits a number of offenses entailing suspension—specified and unconcealed.*";
P_HTM[4596]="*So tasmiṃ bhūmiyaṃ ṭhito purimāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattiyo sarati, aparāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattiyo sarati.**At this point, he remembers offenses committed while on probation for the former offenses, and he remembers offenses committed while on probation for the further offenses.*";
P_HTM[4597]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti—**He considers all this*";
P_HTM[4598]="*‘ahaṃ kho sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ parimāṇampi aparimāṇampi …pe…* **";
P_HTM[4599]="*vavatthitampi sambhinnampi.* **";
P_HTM[4600]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ samodhānaparivāsaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4601]="*Tassa me saṅgho tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ samodhānaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[4602]="*Sohaṃ parivasanto antarā sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ parimāṇāyo appaṭicchannāyo.* **";
P_HTM[4603]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ antarāāpattīnaṃ mūlāyapaṭikassanaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4604]="*Taṃ maṃ saṅgho antarāāpattīnaṃ mūlāya paṭikassi adhammikena kammena kuppena aṭṭhānārahena, adhammena samodhānaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[4605]="*Sohaṃ parivasāmīti maññamāno antarā sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ parimāṇāyo appaṭicchannāyo.* **";
P_HTM[4606]="*Sohaṃ tasmiṃ bhūmiyaṃ ṭhito purimāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattiyo sarāmi, aparāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattiyo sarāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4607]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ purimāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattīnañca aparāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattīnañca mūlāyapaṭikassanaṃ yāceyyaṃ dhammikena kammena akuppena ṭhānārahena, dhammena samodhānaparivāsaṃ;**and thinks, ‘Let me ask the Sangha to send me back to the beginning for all those offenses committed while on probation. And the procedure should be legitimate, irreversible, and fit to stand; the simultaneous probation should be legitimate;*";
P_HTM[4608]="*dhammena mānattaṃ, dhammena abbhānan’ti.**the trial period of six days should be legitimate; and the rehabilitation should be legitimate.’*";
P_HTM[4609]="*So saṅghaṃ purimāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattīnañca, aparāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattīnañca, mūlāyapaṭikassanaṃ yācati dhammikena kammena akuppena ṭhānārahena, dhammena samodhānaparivāsaṃ;**He asks to be sent back to the beginning like this,*";
P_HTM[4610]="*dhammena mānattaṃ, dhammena abbhānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4611]="*Taṃ saṅgho purimāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattīnañca, aparāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattīnañca, mūlāya paṭikassati dhammikena kammena akuppena ṭhānārahena, dhammena samodhānaparivāsaṃ deti;**and the Sangha sends him back to the beginning for those offenses committed while on probation. The legal procedure is legitimate, irreversible, and fit to stand. And the Sangha gives him simultaneous probation legitimately.*";
P_HTM[4612]="*dhammena mānattaṃ deti, dhammena abbheti.**It also gives him the trial period of six days legitimately, and it rehabilitates him legitimately.*";
P_HTM[4613]="*So, bhikkhave, bhikkhu visuddho tāhi āpattīhi.**That monk is purified from those offenses.*";
