P_HTM[4691]="*Sohaṃ tasmiṃ bhūmiyaṃ ṭhito purimāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattiyo sarāmi, aparāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattiyo sarāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4692]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ purimāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattīnañca, aparāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattīnañca, mūlāyapaṭikassanaṃ yāceyyaṃ dhammikena kammena akuppena ṭhānārahena, dhammena samodhānaparivāsaṃ, dhammena mānattaṃ, dhammena abbhānan’ti.**and thinks, ‘Let me ask the Sangha to send me back to the beginning for all those offenses committed while on probation. And the procedure should be legitimate, irreversible, and fit to stand; the simultaneous probation should be legitimate; the trial period of six days should be legitimate; and the rehabilitation should be legitimate.’*";
P_HTM[4693]="*So saṅghaṃ purimāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattīnañca, aparāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattīnañca, mūlāyapaṭikassanaṃ yācati dhammikena kammena akuppena ṭhānārahena, dhammena samodhānaparivāsaṃ, dhammena mānattaṃ, dhammena abbhānaṃ.**He asks to be sent back to the beginning like this,*";
P_HTM[4694]="*Taṃ saṅgho purimāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattīnañca, aparāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattīnañca, mūlāya paṭikassati dhammikena kammena akuppena ṭhānārahena, dhammena samodhānaparivāsaṃ deti, dhammena mānattaṃ deti, dhammena abbheti.**and the Sangha sends him back to the beginning for those offenses committed while on probation. The legal procedure is legitimate, irreversible, and fit to stand. And the Sangha gives him simultaneous probation legitimately. It also gives him the trial period of six days legitimately, and it rehabilitates him legitimately.*";
P_HTM[4695]="*So, bhikkhave, bhikkhu visuddho tāhi āpattīhi.**That monk is purified from those offenses.*";
P_HTM[4696]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjati parimāṇampi aparimāṇampi …pe…**It may be that a monk has committed a number of offenses entailing suspension, both specified and unspecified, both of the same name and of various names, both of the same kind and of various kinds,*";
P_HTM[4697]="*vavatthitampi sambhinnampi.**both of the same sort and of various sorts.*";
P_HTM[4698]="*So saṅghaṃ tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ samodhānaparivāsaṃ yācati.**He asks the Sangha for simultaneous probation for those offenses,*";
P_HTM[4699]="*Tassa saṅgho tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ samodhānaparivāsaṃ deti.**and the Sangha gives him that probation.*";
P_HTM[4700]="*So parivasanto antarā sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjati parimāṇāyopi aparimāṇāyopi paṭicchannāyopi appaṭicchannāyopi.**While on probation, he commits a number of offenses entailing suspension—both concealed and unconcealed and both specified and unspecified.*";
P_HTM[4701]="*So saṅghaṃ antarāāpattīnaṃ mūlāyapaṭikassanaṃ yācati.**He asks the Sangha to send him back to the beginning for those offenses,*";
P_HTM[4702]="*Taṃ saṅgho antarāāpattīnaṃ mūlāya paṭikassati adhammikena kammena kuppena aṭṭhānārahena, adhammena samodhānaparivāsaṃ deti.**and it does. But the legal procedure is illegitimate, reversible, and unfit to stand. And the Sangha gives him simultaneous probation illegitimately.*";
P_HTM[4703]="*So parivasāmīti maññamāno antarā sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjati parimāṇāyopi aparimāṇāyopi paṭicchannāyopi appaṭicchannāyopi.**Thinking that he is on probation, he commits a number of offenses entailing suspension—both concealed and unconcealed and both specified and unspecified.*";
P_HTM[4704]="*So tasmiṃ bhūmiyaṃ ṭhito purimāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattiyo sarati, aparāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattiyo sarati.**At this point he remembers offenses committed while on probation for the former offenses, and he remembers offenses committed while on probation for the further offenses.*";
P_HTM[4705]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti—**He considers all this*";
P_HTM[4706]="*‘ahaṃ kho sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ parimāṇampi aparimāṇampi …pe…* **";
P_HTM[4707]="*vavatthitampi sambhinnampi.* **";
P_HTM[4708]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ samodhānaparivāsaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4709]="*Tassa me saṅgho tāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ samodhānaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[4710]="*Sohaṃ parivasanto antarā sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ parimāṇāyopi aparimāṇāyopi paṭicchannāyopi appaṭicchannāyopi.* **";
P_HTM[4711]="*Sohaṃ saṅghaṃ antarāāpattīnaṃ mūlāyapaṭikassanaṃ yāciṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4712]="*Taṃ maṃ saṅgho antarāāpattīnaṃ mūlāya paṭikassi adhammikena kammena kuppena aṭṭhānārahena, adhammena samodhānaparivāsaṃ adāsi.* **";
P_HTM[4713]="*Sohaṃ parivasāmīti maññamāno antarā sambahulā saṅghādisesā āpattiyo āpajjiṃ parimāṇāyopi aparimāṇāyopi paṭicchannāyopi appaṭicchannāyopi.* **";
P_HTM[4714]="*Sohaṃ tasmiṃ bhūmiyaṃ ṭhito purimāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattiyo sarāmi, aparāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattiyo sarāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4715]="*Yannūnāhaṃ saṅghaṃ purimāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattīnañca, aparāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattīnañca, mūlāyapaṭikassanaṃ yāceyyaṃ dhammikena kammena akuppena ṭhānārahena, dhammena samodhānaparivāsaṃ, dhammena mānattaṃ, dhammena abbhānan’ti.**and thinks, ‘Let me ask the Sangha to send me back to the beginning for all those offenses committed while on probation. And the procedure should be legitimate, irreversible, and fit to stand; the simultaneous probation should be legitimate; the trial period of six days should be legitimate; and the rehabilitation should be legitimate.’*";
P_HTM[4716]="*So saṅghaṃ purimāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattīnañca, aparāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattīnañca, mūlāya paṭikassanaṃ yācati dhammikena kammena akuppena ṭhānārahena, dhammena samodhānaparivāsaṃ, dhammena mānattaṃ, dhammena abbhānaṃ.**He asks to be sent back to the beginning like this,*";
P_HTM[4717]="*Taṃ saṅgho purimāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattīnañca, aparāāpattīnaṃ antarāāpattīnañca, mūlāya paṭikassati dhammikena kammena akuppena ṭhānārahena, dhammena samodhānaparivāsaṃ deti, dhammena mānattaṃ deti, dhammena abbheti.**and the Sangha sends him back to the beginning for those offenses committed while on probation. The legal procedure is legitimate, irreversible, and fit to stand. And the Sangha gives him simultaneous probation legitimately. It also gives him the trial period of six days legitimately, and it rehabilitates him legitimately.*";
P_HTM[4718]="*So, bhikkhave, bhikkhu visuddho tāhi āpattīhi”.**That monk is purified from those offenses.”*";
P_HTM[4719]="*Tatiyanavakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The third group of nine is finished.*";
P_HTM[4720]="*Samuccayakkhandhako tatiyo.**The third chapter containing the collection of processes for the clearing of offenses entailing suspension is finished.*";
P_HTM[4721]="*Tassuddānaṃ* **";
P_HTM[4722]="*Appaṭicchannā ekāha,* **";
P_HTM[4723]="*dvīha tīha catūha ca;* **";
P_HTM[4724]="*Pañcāhapakkhadasannaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[4725]="*āpattimāha mahāmuni.* **";
P_HTM[4726]="*Suddhanto ca vibbhamanto,* **";
P_HTM[4727]="*parimāṇamukhaṃ dve bhikkhū;* **";
P_HTM[4728]="*Tattha saññino dve yathā,* **";
P_HTM[4729]="*vematikā tatheva ca.* **";
P_HTM[4730]="*Missakadiṭṭhino dve ca,* **";
P_HTM[4731]="*asuddhakekadiṭṭhino;* **";
P_HTM[4732]="*Dve ceva suddhadiṭṭhino.* **";
P_HTM[4733]="*Tatheva ca eko chādeti,* **";
P_HTM[4734]="*Atha makkhamatena ca;* **";
P_HTM[4735]="*Ummattakadesanañca,* **";
P_HTM[4736]="*Mūlā aṭṭhārasa visuddhato.* **";
P_HTM[4737]="*Ācariyānaṃ vibhajjapadānaṃ,**The teachers of analytical statements,*";
P_HTM[4738]="*Tambapaṇṇidīpapasādakānaṃ;**Who are the inspiration of Sri Lanka,*";
P_HTM[4739]="*Mahāvihāravāsīnaṃ,**The residents of the Mahāvihāra monastery—*";
P_HTM[4740]="*Vācanā saddhammaṭṭhitiyāti.**This was their words for the longevity of the true Teachings.*";
P_HTM[4741]="*Samuccayakkhandhako niṭṭhito.**The chapter containing the collection of processes for the clearing of offenses entailing suspension is finished.*";
P_HTM[4742]="*4. Samathakkhandhaka **4.  The chapter on the settling of legal issues *";
P_HTM[4743]="*1. Sammukhāvinaya**1. Resolution face-to-face*";
P_HTM[4744]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[4745]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū asammukhībhūtānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ kammāni karonti—**At that time the monks from the group of six did legal procedures—*";
P_HTM[4746]="*tajjanīyampi, niyassampi, pabbājanīyampi, paṭisāraṇīyampi, ukkhepanīyampi.**condemnation, demotion, banishment, reconciliation, and ejection—against monks who were absent.*";
P_HTM[4747]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[4748]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū asammukhībhūtānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ kammāni karissanti—**“How can the monks from the group of six do this?”*";
P_HTM[4749]="*tajjanīyampi, niyassampi, pabbājanīyampi, paṭisāraṇīyampi, ukkhepanīyampī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4750]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha of monks gathered and questioned them:*";
P_HTM[4751]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū asammukhībhūtānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ kammāni karonti—**“Is it true, monks, that the monks from the group of six are doing this?”*";
P_HTM[4752]="*tajjanīyampi, niyassampi, pabbājanīyampi, paṭisāraṇīyampi, ukkhepanīyampī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[4753]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[4754]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—**The Buddha criticized them,*";
P_HTM[4755]="*“ananucchavikaṃ, bhikkhave, tesaṃ moghapurisānaṃ ananulomikaṃ appatirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ akaraṇīyaṃ.**“It’s not suitable for those foolish men, it’s not proper, it’s not worthy of a monastic, it’s not allowable, it’s not to be done.*";
P_HTM[4756]="*Kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā asammukhībhūtānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ kammāni karissanti—**How can they act like this?*";
P_HTM[4757]="*tajjanīyampi, niyassampi, pabbājanīyampi, paṭisāraṇīyampi, ukkhepanīyampi.* **";
P_HTM[4758]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[4759]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[4760]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[4761]="*“Na, bhikkhave, asammukhībhūtānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ kammaṃ kātabbaṃ—**“You should not do legal procedures—*";
P_HTM[4762]="*tajjanīyaṃ vā, niyassaṃ vā, pabbājanīyaṃ vā, paṭisāraṇīyaṃ vā, ukkhepanīyaṃ vā.**condemnation, demotion, banishment, reconciliation, or ejection—against monks who are absent.*";
P_HTM[4763]="*Yo kareyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4764]="*Adhammavādī puggalo adhammavādī sambahulā adhammavādī saṅgho.**An individual who speaks contrary to the Teaching; several people who speak contrary to the Teaching; a sangha that speaks contrary to the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[4765]="*Dhammavādī puggalo dhammavādī sambahulā dhammavādī saṅgho.**An individual who speaks in accordance with the Teaching; several people who speak in accordance with the Teaching; a sangha that speaks in accordance with the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[4766]="*1.1. Kaṇhapakkhanavaka**1.1 The group of nine on the dark side*";
P_HTM[4767]="*Adhammavādī puggalo dhammavādiṃ puggalaṃ saññāpeti nijjhāpeti pekkheti anupekkheti dasseti anudasseti—**“An individual who speaks contrary to the Teaching persuades an individual who speaks in accordance with the Teaching—convinces him, makes him see, makes him consider, shows him, teaches him:*";
P_HTM[4768]="*‘ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanaṃ, imaṃ gaṇhāhi, imaṃ rocehī’ti.**‘This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction; learn this, accept this.’*";
P_HTM[4769]="*Evañcetaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati, adhammena vūpasammati sammukhāvinayapatirūpakena.**If a legal issue is resolved like this, it is resolved illegitimately by a face-to-face-like resolution.*";
P_HTM[4770]="*Adhammavādī puggalo dhammavādī sambahule saññāpeti nijjhāpeti pekkheti anupekkheti dasseti anudasseti—**An individual who speaks contrary to the Teaching persuades several people who speak in accordance with the Teaching—convinces them, makes them see, makes them consider, shows them, teaches them:*";
P_HTM[4771]="*‘ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanaṃ, imaṃ gaṇhatha, imaṃ rocethā’ti.**‘This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction; learn this, accept this.’*";
P_HTM[4772]="*Evañcetaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati, adhammena vūpasammati sammukhāvinayapatirūpakena.**If a legal issue is resolved like this, it is resolved illegitimately by a face-to-face-like resolution.*";
