P_HTM[4801]="*Evañcetaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati, dhammena vūpasammati sammukhāvinayena.**If a legal issue is resolved like this, it is resolved legitimately by resolution face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[4802]="*Dhammavādī puggalo adhammavādiṃ saṅghaṃ saññāpeti nijjhāpeti pekkheti anupekkheti dasseti anudasseti—**An individual who speaks in accordance with the Teaching persuades a sangha that speaks contrary to the Teaching—convinces it, makes it see, makes it consider, shows it, teaches it:*";
P_HTM[4803]="*‘ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanaṃ, imaṃ gaṇhāhi, imaṃ rocehī’ti.**‘This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction; learn this, accept this.’*";
P_HTM[4804]="*Evañcetaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati, dhammena vūpasammati sammukhāvinayena.**If a legal issue is resolved like this, it is resolved legitimately by resolution face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[4805]="*Dhammavādī sambahulā adhammavādiṃ puggalaṃ saññāpenti nijjhāpenti pekkhenti anupekkhenti dassenti anudassenti—**“Several people who speak in accordance with the Teaching persuade an individual who speaks contrary to the Teaching—convince him, make him see, make him consider, show him, teach him:*";
P_HTM[4806]="*‘ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanaṃ, imaṃ gaṇhāhi, imaṃ rocehī’ti.**‘This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction; learn this, accept this.’*";
P_HTM[4807]="*Evañcetaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati, dhammena vūpasammati sammukhāvinayena.**If a legal issue is resolved like this, it is resolved legitimately by resolution face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[4808]="*Dhammavādī sambahulā adhammavādī sambahule saññāpenti nijjhāpenti pekkhenti anupekkhenti dassenti anudassenti—**Several people who speak in accordance with the Teaching persuade several people who speak contrary to the Teaching—convince them, make them see, make them consider, show them, teach them:*";
P_HTM[4809]="*‘ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanaṃ, imaṃ gaṇhatha, imaṃ rocethā’ti.**‘This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction; learn this, accept this.’*";
P_HTM[4810]="*Evañcetaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati, dhammena vūpasammati sammukhāvinayena.**If a legal issue is resolved like this, it is resolved legitimately by resolution face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[4811]="*Dhammavādī sambahulā adhammavādiṃ saṅghaṃ saññāpenti nijjhāpenti pekkhenti anupekkhenti dassenti anudassenti—**Several people who speak in accordance with the Teaching persuade a sangha that speaks contrary to the Teaching—convince it, make it see, make it consider, show it, teach it:*";
P_HTM[4812]="*‘ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanaṃ, imaṃ gaṇhāhi, imaṃ rocehī’ti.**‘This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction; learn this, accept this.’*";
P_HTM[4813]="*Evañcetaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati, dhammena vūpasammati sammukhāvinayena.**If a legal issue is resolved like this, it is resolved legitimately by resolution face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[4814]="*Dhammavādī saṅgho adhammavādiṃ puggalaṃ saññāpeti nijjhāpeti pekkheti anupekkheti dasseti anudasseti—**“A sangha that speaks in accordance with the Teaching persuades an individual who speaks contrary to the Teaching—convinces him, makes him see, makes him consider, shows him, teaches him:*";
P_HTM[4815]="*‘ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanaṃ, imaṃ gaṇhāhi, imaṃ rocehī’ti.**‘This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction; learn this, accept this.’*";
P_HTM[4816]="*Evañcetaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati, dhammena vūpasammati sammukhāvinayena.**If a legal issue is resolved like this, it is resolved legitimately by resolution face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[4817]="*Dhammavādī saṅgho adhammavādī sambahule saññāpeti nijjhāpeti pekkheti anupekkheti dasseti anudasseti—**A sangha that speaks in accordance with the Teaching persuades several people who speak contrary to the Teaching—convinces them, makes them see, makes them consider, shows them, teaches them:*";
P_HTM[4818]="*‘ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanaṃ, imaṃ gaṇhatha, imaṃ rocethā’ti.**‘This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction; learn this, accept this.’*";
P_HTM[4819]="*Evañcetaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati, dhammena vūpasammati sammukhāvinayena.**If a legal issue is resolved like this, it is resolved legitimately by resolution face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[4820]="*Dhammavādī saṅgho adhammavādiṃ saṅghaṃ saññāpeti nijjhāpeti pekkheti anupekkheti dasseti anudasseti—**A sangha that speaks in accordance with the Teaching persuades a sangha that speaks contrary to the Teaching—convinces it, makes it see, makes it consider, shows it, teaches it:*";
P_HTM[4821]="*‘ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanaṃ, imaṃ gaṇhāhi, imaṃ rocehī’ti.**‘This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction; learn this, accept this.’*";
P_HTM[4822]="*Evañcetaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati, dhammena vūpasammati sammukhāvinayenā”ti.**If a legal issue is resolved like this, it is resolved legitimately by resolution face-to-face.”*";
P_HTM[4823]="*Sukkapakkhanavakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of nine on the bright side is finished.*";
P_HTM[4824]="*2. Sativinaya**2. Resolution through recollection*";
P_HTM[4825]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove,*";
P_HTM[4826]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmatā dabbena mallaputtena jātiyā sattavassena arahattaṃ sacchikataṃ hoti.**Venerable Dabba the Mallian realized perfection at the age of seven.*";
P_HTM[4827]="*Yaṃ kiñci sāvakena pattabbaṃ sabbaṃ tena anuppattaṃ hoti.**He had achieved all there is to achieve by a disciple*";
P_HTM[4828]="*Natthi cassa kiñci uttari karaṇīyaṃ, katassa vā paticayo.**and had nothing further to do.*";
P_HTM[4829]="*Atha kho āyasmato dabbassa mallaputtassa rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi—**While he was in seclusion he reflected on this,*";
P_HTM[4830]="*“mayā kho jātiyā sattavassena arahattaṃ sacchikataṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4831]="*Yaṃ kiñci sāvakena pattabbaṃ sabbaṃ mayā anuppattaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4832]="*Natthi ca me kiñci uttarikaraṇīyaṃ, katassa vā paticayo.* **";
P_HTM[4833]="*Kiṃ nu kho ahaṃ saṅghassa veyyāvaccaṃ kareyyan”ti.**and he thought, “How can I be of service to the Sangha?*";
P_HTM[4834]="*Atha kho āyasmato dabbassa mallaputtassa etadahosi—* **";
P_HTM[4835]="*“yannūnāhaṃ saṅghassa senāsanañca paññapeyyaṃ bhattāni ca uddiseyyan”ti.**Why donʼt I assign the dwellings and designate the meals?”*";
P_HTM[4836]="*Atha kho āyasmā dabbo mallaputto sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**In the evening Dabba came out of seclusion and went to the Buddha. He bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[4837]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā dabbo mallaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[4838]="*“idha mayhaṃ, bhante, rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi—**“Venerable Sir, while I was in seclusion I reflected that*";
P_HTM[4839]="*‘mayā kho jātiyā sattavassena arahattaṃ sacchikataṃ.**I’ve achieved all there is to achieve by a disciple,*";
P_HTM[4840]="*Yaṃ kiñci sāvakena pattabbaṃ, sabbaṃ mayā anuppattaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4841]="*Natthi ca me kiñci uttarikaraṇīyaṃ, katassa vā paticayo.* **";
P_HTM[4842]="*Kiṃ nu kho ahaṃ saṅghassa veyyāvaccaṃ kareyyan’ti?**and I was wondering how I could be of service to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[4843]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi—**I thought,*";
P_HTM[4844]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ saṅghassa senāsanañca paññapeyyaṃ bhattāni ca uddiseyyan’ti.**ʻWhy don’t I assign the dwellings and designate the meals?ʼ”*";
P_HTM[4845]="*Icchāmahaṃ, bhante, saṅghassa senāsanañca paññāpetuṃ bhattāni ca uddisitun”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4846]="*“Sādhu sādhu, dabba.**“Good, good, Dabba,*";
P_HTM[4847]="*Tena hi tvaṃ, dabba, saṅghassa senāsanañca paññapehi bhattāni ca uddisāhī”ti.**please do so.”*";
P_HTM[4848]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā dabbo mallaputto bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes.”*";
P_HTM[4849]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[4850]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ senāsanapaññāpakañca bhattuddesakañca sammannatu.**“Monks, the Sangha should appoint Dabba the Mallian as the assigner of dwellings and the designator of meals.*";
P_HTM[4851]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sammannitabbo.**And he should be appointed like this.*";
P_HTM[4852]="*Paṭhamaṃ dabbo mallaputto yācitabbo.**First Dabba should be asked.*";
P_HTM[4853]="*Yācitvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[4854]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[4855]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ senāsanapaññāpakañca bhattuddesakañca sammanneyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, it should appoint Venerable Dabba the Mallian as assigner of dwellings and designator of meals.*";
P_HTM[4856]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[4857]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[4858]="*Saṅgho āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ senāsanapaññāpakañca bhattuddesakañca sammannati.**The Sangha appoints Venerable Dabba the Mallian as assigner of dwellings and designator of meals.*";
P_HTM[4859]="*Yassāyasmato khamati āyasmato dabbassa mallaputtassa senāsanapaññāpakassa ca bhattuddesakassa ca sammuti, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of appointing Venerable Dabba as assigner of dwellings and designator of meals should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[4860]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[4861]="*Sammato saṅghena āyasmā dabbo mallaputto senāsanapaññāpako ca bhattuddesako ca.**The Sangha has appointed Venerable Dabba the Mallian as assigner of dwellings and designator of meals.*";
P_HTM[4862]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[4863]="*Sammato ca panāyasmā dabbo mallaputto sabhāgānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ ekajjhaṃ senāsanaṃ paññapeti.**Dabba assigned dwellings to the monks according to their character.*";
P_HTM[4864]="*Ye te bhikkhū suttantikā tesaṃ ekajjhaṃ senāsanaṃ paññapeti—**He assigned dwellings in the same place to those monks who were experts on the discourse, thinking,*";
P_HTM[4865]="*“te aññamaññaṃ suttantaṃ saṅgāyissantī”ti.**“They’ll recite the discourses together.”*";
P_HTM[4866]="*Ye te bhikkhū vinayadharā tesaṃ ekajjhaṃ senāsanaṃ paññapeti—**And he did likewise for the experts on Monastic Law, thinking,*";
P_HTM[4867]="*“te aññamaññaṃ vinayaṃ vinicchinissantī”ti.**“They’ll deliberate on the Monastic Law;”*";
P_HTM[4868]="*Ye te bhikkhū dhammakathikā tesaṃ ekajjhaṃ senāsanaṃ paññapeti—**for the expounders of the Teaching, thinking,*";
P_HTM[4869]="*“te aññamaññaṃ dhammaṃ sākacchissantī”ti.**“They’ll discuss the Teaching;”*";
P_HTM[4870]="*Ye te bhikkhū jhāyino tesaṃ ekajjhaṃ senāsanaṃ paññapeti—**for the meditators, thinking,*";
P_HTM[4871]="*“te aññamaññaṃ na byābādhissantī”ti.**“They won’t disturb one another;”*";
P_HTM[4872]="*Ye te bhikkhū tiracchānakathikā kāyadaḷhibahulā viharanti tesampi ekajjhaṃ senāsanaṃ paññapeti—**and for the gossips and the body-builders, thinking,*";
P_HTM[4873]="*“imāyapime āyasmanto ratiyā acchissantī”ti.**“In this way even these venerables will be happy.”*";
P_HTM[4874]="*Yepi te bhikkhū vikāle āgacchanti tesampi tejodhātuṃ samāpajjitvā teneva ālokena senāsanaṃ paññapeti;**When monks arrived at night, he entered the fire element and assigned dwellings with the help of that light.*";
P_HTM[4875]="*apissu bhikkhū sañcicca vikāle āgacchanti—**Monks even arrived late on purpose,*";
P_HTM[4876]="*“mayaṃ āyasmato dabbassa mallaputtassa iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ passissāmā”ti.**hoping to see the marvel of Dabba’s supernormal powers.*";
P_HTM[4877]="*Te āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadanti—**They would approach Dabba and say,*";
P_HTM[4878]="*“amhākaṃ, āvuso dabba, senāsanaṃ paññapehī”ti.**“Venerable Dabba, please assign us a dwelling.”*";
P_HTM[4879]="*Te āyasmā dabbo mallaputto evaṃ vadeti—* **";
P_HTM[4880]="*“kattha āyasmantā icchanti kattha paññapemī”ti?**“Where would you like to stay?”*";
P_HTM[4881]="*Te sañcicca dūre apadisanti—**They would intentionally suggest somewhere far away:*";
P_HTM[4882]="*“amhākaṃ, āvuso dabba, gijjhakūṭe pabbate senāsanaṃ paññapehi.**“On the Vulture Peak,”*";
P_HTM[4883]="*Amhākaṃ, āvuso, corapapāte senāsanaṃ paññapehi.**“At Robbers’ Cliff,”*";
P_HTM[4884]="*Amhākaṃ, āvuso, isigilipasse kāḷasilāyaṃ senāsanaṃ paññapehi.**“On Black Rock on the slope of Mount Isigili,”*";
P_HTM[4885]="*Amhākaṃ, āvuso, vebhārapasse sattapaṇṇiguhāyaṃ senāsanaṃ paññapehi.**“In the Sattapaṇṇi Cave on the slope of Mount Vebhāra,”*";
P_HTM[4886]="*Amhākaṃ, āvuso, sītavane sappasoṇḍikapabbhāre senāsanaṃ paññapehi.**“In Cool Grove on the hill at the Snake’s Pool,”*";
P_HTM[4887]="*Amhākaṃ, āvuso, gotamakakandarāyaṃ senāsanaṃ paññapehi.**“At Gotamaka Gorge,”*";
P_HTM[4888]="*Amhākaṃ, āvuso, tindukakandarāyaṃ senāsanaṃ paññapehi.**“At Tinduka Gorge,”*";
P_HTM[4889]="*Amhākaṃ, āvuso, tapodakandarāyaṃ senāsanaṃ paññapehi.**“At Tapoda Gorge,”*";
P_HTM[4890]="*Amhākaṃ, āvuso, tapodārāme senāsanaṃ paññapehi.**“In Tapoda Park,”*";
P_HTM[4891]="*Amhākaṃ, āvuso, jīvakambavane senāsanaṃ paññapehi.**“In Jīvaka’s Mango Grove,”*";
P_HTM[4892]="*Amhākaṃ, āvuso, maddakucchimhi migadāye senāsanaṃ paññapehī”ti.**“In the deer park at Maddakucchi.”*";
P_HTM[4893]="*Tesaṃ āyasmā dabbo mallaputto tejodhātuṃ samāpajjitvā aṅguliyā jalamānāya purato purato gacchati.**Dabba then entered the fire element, and with his finger glowing, he walked in front of those monks.*";
P_HTM[4894]="*Tepi teneva ālokena āyasmato dabbassa mallaputtassa piṭṭhito piṭṭhito gacchanti.**They followed behind him with the help of that light.*";
P_HTM[4895]="*Tesaṃ āyasmā dabbo mallaputto evaṃ senāsanaṃ paññapeti—**And he would assign them dwellings:*";
P_HTM[4896]="*“ayaṃ mañco, idaṃ pīṭhaṃ, ayaṃ bhisi, idaṃ bibbohanaṃ, idaṃ vaccaṭṭhānaṃ, idaṃ passāvaṭṭhānaṃ, idaṃ pānīyaṃ, idaṃ paribhojanīyaṃ, ayaṃ kattaradaṇḍo, idaṃ saṅghassa katikasaṇṭhānaṃ, imaṃ kālaṃ pavisitabbaṃ, imaṃ kālaṃ nikkhamitabban”ti.**“This is the bed, this the bench, this the mattress, this the pillow, this the place for defecating, this the place for urinating, this the water for drinking, this the water for washing, this the walking stick; these are the Sangha’s agreements concerning the right time to enter and the right time to leave.”*";
P_HTM[4897]="*Tesaṃ āyasmā dabbo mallaputto evaṃ senāsanaṃ paññapetvā punadeva veḷuvanaṃ paccāgacchati.**Dabba then returned to the Bamboo Grove.*";
P_HTM[4898]="*Tena kho pana samayena mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū navakā ceva honti appapuññā ca.**At that time the monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka were only newly ordained. They had little merit,*";
P_HTM[4899]="*Yāni saṅghassa lāmakāni senāsanāni tāni tesaṃ pāpuṇanti lāmakāni ca bhattāni.**getting inferior dwellings and meals.*";
P_HTM[4900]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājagahe manussā icchanti therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhisaṅkhārikaṃ piṇḍapātaṃ dātuṃ—**The people of Rājagaha were keen to give specially prepared almsfood to the senior monks—*";
P_HTM[4901]="*sappimpi, telampi, uttaribhaṅgampi.**ghee, oil, and special curries—*";
P_HTM[4902]="*Mettiyabhūmajakānaṃ pana bhikkhūnaṃ pākatikaṃ denti—**but to the monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka they gave ordinary food of*";
P_HTM[4903]="*yathārandhaṃ kaṇājakaṃ bilaṅgadutiyaṃ.**porridge and broken rice.*";
P_HTM[4904]="*Te pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantā there bhikkhū pucchanti—**After the meal, when they had returned from almsround, they asked the senior monks,*";
P_HTM[4905]="*“tumhākaṃ, āvuso, bhattagge kiṃ ahosi, tumhākaṃ kiṃ ahosī”ti?**“What did you get at the dining hall?”*";
P_HTM[4906]="*Ekacce therā evaṃ vadanti—**Some said,*";
P_HTM[4907]="*“amhākaṃ, āvuso, sappi ahosi, telaṃ ahosi, uttaribhaṅgaṃ ahosī”ti.**“We got ghee, oil, and special curries.”*";
P_HTM[4908]="*Mettiyabhūmajakā pana bhikkhū evaṃ vadanti—**But the monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka said,*";
P_HTM[4909]="*“amhākaṃ, āvuso, na kiñci ahosi—**“We didn’t get anything*";
P_HTM[4910]="*pākatikaṃ yathārandhaṃ kaṇājakaṃ bilaṅgadutiyan”ti.**except ordinary food of porridge and broken rice.”*";
P_HTM[4911]="*Tena kho pana samayena kalyāṇabhattiko gahapati saṅghassa catukkabhattaṃ deti niccabhattaṃ.**At that time there was a householder who gave a regular meal of fine food to four monks.*";
P_HTM[4912]="*So bhattagge saputtadāro upatiṭṭhitvā parivisati—**He made his offering in the dining hall together with his wives and children.*";
P_HTM[4913]="*aññe odanena pucchanti, aññe sūpena pucchanti, aññe telena pucchanti, aññe uttaribhaṅgena pucchanti.**Some of them offered rice, some bean curry, some oil, and some special curries.*";
P_HTM[4914]="*Tena kho pana samayena kalyāṇabhattikassa gahapatino bhattaṃ svātanāya mettiyabhūmajakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ uddiṭṭhaṃ hoti.**On one occasion the meal to be given by this householder on the following day had been designated to the monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka.*";
P_HTM[4915]="*Atha kho kalyāṇabhattiko gahapati ārāmaṃ agamāsi kenacideva karaṇīyena.**Just then that householder went to the monastery on some business.*";
P_HTM[4916]="*So yenāyasmā dabbo mallaputto tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**He approached Dabba, bowed, and sat down.*";
P_HTM[4917]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho kalyāṇabhattikaṃ gahapatiṃ āyasmā dabbo mallaputto dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi.**And Dabba instructed, inspired, and gladdened him with a teaching.*";
P_HTM[4918]="*Atha kho kalyāṇabhattiko gahapati āyasmatā dabbena mallaputtena dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ etadavoca—**After the talk, he asked Dabba,*";
P_HTM[4919]="*“kassa, bhante, amhākaṃ ghare svātanāya bhattaṃ uddiṭṭhan”ti?**“Sir, who has been designated to receive tomorrow’s meal in our house?”*";
P_HTM[4920]="*“Mettiyabhūmajakānaṃ kho, gahapati, bhikkhūnaṃ tumhākaṃ ghare svātanāya bhattaṃ uddiṭṭhan”ti.**“Mettiya and Bhūmajaka.”*";
P_HTM[4921]="*Atha kho kalyāṇabhattiko gahapati anattamano ahosi.**He was disappointed,*";
P_HTM[4922]="*Kathañhi nāma pāpabhikkhū amhākaṃ ghare bhuñjissantīti gharaṃ gantvā dāsiṃ āṇāpesi—**and thought, “Why should bad monks eat in our house?” After returning to his house, he told a female slave,*";
P_HTM[4923]="*“ye, je, sve bhattikā āgacchanti te koṭṭhake āsanaṃ paññapetvā kaṇājakena bilaṅgadutiyena parivisā”ti.**“For those who are coming for tomorrow’s meal, prepare seats at the gateway and serve them broken rice and porridge.”*";
P_HTM[4924]="*“Evaṃ, ayyā”ti kho sā dāsī kalyāṇabhattikassa gahapatino paccassosi.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4925]="*Atha kho mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū—**The monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka said to each other,*";
P_HTM[4926]="*“hiyyo kho, āvuso, amhākaṃ kalyāṇabhattikassa gahapatino bhattaṃ uddiṭṭhaṃ;**“Yesterday we were designated a meal from the householder who offers fine food.*";
P_HTM[4927]="*sve amhe kalyāṇabhattiko gahapati saputtadāro upatiṭṭhitvā parivisissati;**Tomorrow he’ll serve us together with his wives and children.*";
P_HTM[4928]="*aññe odanena pucchissanti, aññe sūpena pucchissanti, aññe telena pucchissanti, aññe uttaribhaṅgena pucchissantī”ti.**Some of them will offer us rice, some bean curry, some oil, and some special curries.”*";
P_HTM[4929]="*Te teneva somanassena na cittarūpaṃ rattiyā supiṃsu.**And because they were excited, they did not sleep properly that night.*";
P_HTM[4930]="*Atha kho mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena kalyāṇabhattikassa gahapatino nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu.**The following morning they robed up, took their bowls and robes, and went to the house of that householder.*";
P_HTM[4931]="*Addasā kho sā dāsī mettiyabhūmajake bhikkhū dūratova āgacchante;**When the female slave saw them coming,*";
P_HTM[4932]="*disvāna koṭṭhake āsanaṃ paññapetvā mettiyabhūmajake bhikkhū etadavoca—**she prepared seats at the gateway and said to them,*";
P_HTM[4933]="*“nisīdatha, bhante”ti.**“Please sit, Venerables.”*";
P_HTM[4934]="*Atha kho mettiyabhūmajakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**They thought,*";
P_HTM[4935]="*“nissaṃsayaṃ kho na tāva bhattaṃ siddhaṃ bhavissati yathā mayaṃ koṭṭhake nisīdāpiyāmā”ti.**“The meal can’t be ready, since we’re given seats at the gateway.”*";
P_HTM[4936]="*Atha kho sā dāsī kaṇājakena bilaṅgadutiyena upagañchi—**She then brought them broken rice and porridge, and said,*";
P_HTM[4937]="*“bhuñjatha, bhante”ti.**“Eat, Sirs.”*";
P_HTM[4938]="*“Mayaṃ kho, bhagini, niccabhattikā”ti.**“But, Sister, we’ve come for the regular meal.”*";
P_HTM[4939]="*“Jānāmi ayyā niccabhattikāti.**“I know.*";
P_HTM[4940]="*Api cāhaṃ hiyyova gahapatinā āṇattā—**But yesterday I was told by the head of our household*";
P_HTM[4941]="*‘ye, je, sve bhattikā āgacchanti, te koṭṭhake āsanaṃ paññapetvā kaṇājakena bilaṅgadutiyena parivisā’ti.**to serve you like this.*";
P_HTM[4942]="*Bhuñjatha, bhante”ti.**Please eat.”*";
P_HTM[4943]="*Atha kho mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū—**They said to each other,*";
P_HTM[4944]="*“hiyyo kho, āvuso, kalyāṇabhattiko gahapati ārāmaṃ agamāsi dabbassa mallaputtassa santike.**“Yesterday this householder came to the monastery and spoke with Dabba.*";
P_HTM[4945]="*Nissaṃsayaṃ kho mayaṃ dabbena mallaputtena gahapatino antare paribhinnā”ti.**Dabba must be responsible for this split between the householder and us.”*";
P_HTM[4946]="*Te teneva domanassena na cittarūpaṃ bhuñjiṃsu.**And because they were dejected, they did not eat as much as they had intended.*";
P_HTM[4947]="*Atha kho mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantā ārāmaṃ gantvā pattacīvaraṃ paṭisāmetvā bahārāmakoṭṭhake saṅghāṭipallatthikāya nisīdiṃsu tuṇhībhūtā maṅkubhūtā pattakkhandhā adhomukhā pajjhāyantā appaṭibhānā.**After the meal they returned to the monastery, put their bowls and robes away, and sat outside the monastery gateway, using their upper robe as a back-and-knee strap. They were silent and humiliated, their shoulders drooping and their heads down, glum and speechless.*";
P_HTM[4948]="*Atha kho mettiyā bhikkhunī yena mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā mettiyabhūmajake bhikkhū etadavoca—**Just then the nun Mettiyā came to them and said,*";
P_HTM[4949]="*“vandāmi, ayyā”ti.**“My respectful greetings to you, Venerables.”*";
P_HTM[4950]="*Evaṃ vutte, mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū nālapiṃsu.**But they did not respond.*";
P_HTM[4951]="*Dutiyampi kho …pe…**A second time and*";
P_HTM[4952]="*tatiyampi kho mettiyā bhikkhunī mettiyabhūmajake bhikkhū etadavoca—**a third time she said the same thing,*";
P_HTM[4953]="*“vandāmi, ayyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4954]="*Tatiyampi kho mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū nālapiṃsu.**but they still did not respond.*";
P_HTM[4955]="*“Kyāhaṃ ayyānaṃ aparajjhāmi?**“Have I done something wrong?*";
P_HTM[4956]="*Kissa maṃ ayyā nālapantī”ti?**Why don’t you respond?”*";
P_HTM[4957]="*“Tathā hi pana tvaṃ, bhagini, amhe dabbena mallaputtena viheṭhiyamāne ajjhupekkhasī”ti?**“It’s because we’ve been badly treated by Dabba the Mallian, and you’re not taking an interest.”*";
P_HTM[4958]="*“Kyāhaṃ, ayyā, karomī”ti?**“But what can I do?”*";
P_HTM[4959]="*“Sace kho tvaṃ, bhagini, iccheyyāsi, ajjeva bhagavā āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ nāsāpeyyā”ti.**“If you like, you could make the Buddha expel Dabba.”*";
P_HTM[4960]="*“Kyāhaṃ, ayyā, karomi?* **";
P_HTM[4961]="*Kiṃ mayā sakkā kātun”ti?**“And how can I do that?”*";
P_HTM[4962]="*“Ehi tvaṃ, bhagini, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkama, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ evaṃ vadehi—**“Go to the Buddha and say,*";
P_HTM[4963]="*‘idaṃ, bhante, nacchannaṃ nappatirūpaṃ, yāyaṃ, bhante, disā abhayā anītikā anupaddavā sāyaṃ disā sabhayā saītikā saupaddavā;**‘Venerable Sir, this is not proper or appropriate. There’s fear, distress, and oppression in this district, where none of these should exist.*";
P_HTM[4964]="*yato nivātaṃ tato savātaṃ;**From where one would expect security, there’s insecurity.*";
P_HTM[4965]="*udakaṃ maññe ādittaṃ;**It’s as if water is burning.*";
P_HTM[4966]="*ayyenamhi dabbena mallaputtena dūsitā’”ti.**Venerable Dabba the Mallian has raped me.’”*";
P_HTM[4967]="*“Evaṃ, ayyā”ti kho mettiyā bhikkhunī mettiyabhūmajakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi.**Saying, “Alright, Venerables,” she went to the Buddha, bowed,*";
P_HTM[4968]="*Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho mettiyā bhikkhunī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and repeated*";
P_HTM[4969]="*“idaṃ, bhante, nacchannaṃ nappatirūpaṃ, yāyaṃ, bhante, disā abhayā anītikā anupaddavā sāyaṃ disā sabhayā saītikā saupaddavā;**what she had been told to say.*";
P_HTM[4970]="*yato nivātaṃ tato savātaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4971]="*udakaṃ maññe ādittaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4972]="*ayyenamhi dabbena mallaputtena dūsitā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4973]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned Dabba:*";
P_HTM[4974]="*“sarasi tvaṃ, dabba, evarūpaṃ kattā yathāyaṃ bhikkhunī āhā”ti?**“Dabba, do you remember doing as the nun Mettiyā says?”*";
P_HTM[4975]="*“Yathā maṃ, bhante, bhagavā jānātī”ti.**“Venerable Sir, you know what I’m like.”*";
P_HTM[4976]="*Dutiyampi kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ etadavoca—**A second*";
P_HTM[4977]="*“sarasi tvaṃ, dabba, evarūpaṃ kattā yathāyaṃ bhikkhunī āhā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[4978]="*“Yathā maṃ, bhante, bhagavā jānātī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4979]="*Tatiyampi kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ etadavoca—**and a third time the Buddha asked*";
P_HTM[4980]="*“sarasi tvaṃ, dabba, evarūpaṃ kattā yathāyaṃ bhikkhunī āhā”ti?**the same question*";
P_HTM[4981]="*“Yathā maṃ, bhante, bhagavā jānātī”ti.**and got the same response.*";
P_HTM[4982]="*“Na kho, dabba, dabbā evaṃ nibbeṭhenti.**He then said, “Dabba, the Dabbas don’t give such evasive answers.*";
P_HTM[4983]="*Sace tayā kataṃ katanti vadehi.**If it was done by you, say so;*";
P_HTM[4984]="*Sace akataṃ akatanti vadehī”ti.**if it wasn’t, then say that.”*";
P_HTM[4985]="*“Yatohaṃ, bhante, jāto nābhijānāmi supinantenapi methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevitā, pageva jāgaro”ti.**“Since I was born, Sir, I don’t recall having sexual intercourse even in a dream, let alone when awake.”*";
P_HTM[4986]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi—**The Buddha addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[4987]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, mettiyaṃ bhikkhuniṃ nāsetha.**“Well then, monks, expel the nun Mettiyā,*";
P_HTM[4988]="*Ime ca bhikkhū anuyuñjathā”ti.**and call these monks to account.”*";
P_HTM[4989]="*Idaṃ vatvā bhagavā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ pāvisi.**The Buddha then got up from his seat and entered his dwelling.*";
P_HTM[4990]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū mettiyaṃ bhikkhuniṃ nāsesuṃ.**When the monks had expelled the nun Mettiyā,*";
P_HTM[4991]="*Atha kho mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū te bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—**the monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka said to them,*";
P_HTM[4992]="*“māvuso, mettiyaṃ bhikkhuniṃ nāsetha, na sā kiñci aparajjhati;**“Don’t expel the nun Mettiyā; she’s done nothing wrong.*";
P_HTM[4993]="*amhehi sā ussāhitā kupitehi anattamanehi cāvanādhippāyehī”ti.**She was urged on by us. We were angry and displeased, and trying to get Dabba to leave the monastic life.”*";
P_HTM[4994]="*“Kiṃ pana tumhe, āvuso, āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā anuddhaṃsethā”ti?**“But did you groundlessly charge Venerable Dabba with failure in morality?”*";
P_HTM[4995]="*“Evamāvuso”ti.**“Yes.”*";
P_HTM[4996]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[4997]="*“kathañhi nāma mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā anuddhaṃsessantī”ti.**“How could the monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka groundlessly charge Venerable Dabba with failure in morality?”*";
P_HTM[4998]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They rebuked those monks in many ways and then told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha of monks gathered and questioned those monks:*";
P_HTM[4999]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā anuddhaṃsentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[5000]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5001]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after rebuking them …*";
P_HTM[5002]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[5003]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho dabbassa mallaputtassa sativepullappattassa sativinayaṃ detu.**“Well then, because of his great clarity of memory, grant resolution through recollection to Dabba the Mallian.*";
P_HTM[5004]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbo—**And it should be granted like this:*";
P_HTM[5005]="*tena, bhikkhave, dabbena mallaputtena saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā, ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā, vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā, ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā, añjaliṃ paggahetvā, evamassa vacanīyo—**Dabba should approach the Sangha, put his upper robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and say:*";
P_HTM[5006]="*‘ime maṃ, bhante, mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā anuddhaṃsenti.**‘Venerables, these monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka are groundlessly charging me with failure in morality.*";
P_HTM[5007]="*Sohaṃ, bhante, sativepullappatto saṅghaṃ sativinayaṃ yācāmī’ti.**Because of my great clarity of memory, I ask the Sangha for resolution through recollection.*";
P_HTM[5008]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbo.**Venerables, these monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka are groundlessly charging me with failure in morality. Because of my great clarity of memory, for the second time I ask the Sangha for resolution through recollection.*";
P_HTM[5009]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbo—* **";
P_HTM[5010]="*‘ime maṃ, bhante, mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā anuddhaṃsenti.**Venerables, these monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka are groundlessly charging me with failure in morality.*";
P_HTM[5011]="*Sohaṃ sativepullappatto tatiyampi, bhante, saṅghaṃ sativinayaṃ yācāmī’ti.**Because of my great clarity of memory, for the third time I ask the Sangha for resolution through recollection.’*";
P_HTM[5012]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[5013]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5014]="*Ime mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā anuddhaṃsenti.**These monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka are groundlessly charging Venerable Dabba the Mallian with failure in morality.*";
P_HTM[5015]="*Āyasmā dabbo mallaputto sativepullappatto saṅghaṃ sativinayaṃ yācati.**Because of his great clarity of memory, Dabba is asking the Sangha for resolution through recollection.*";
P_HTM[5016]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho āyasmato dabbassa mallaputtassa sativepullappattassa sativinayaṃ dadeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should grant resolution through recollection to Dabba.*";
P_HTM[5017]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[5018]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5019]="*Ime mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā anuddhaṃsenti.**These monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka are groundlessly charging Venerable Dabba the Mallian with failure in morality.*";
P_HTM[5020]="*Āyasmā dabbo mallaputto sativepullappatto saṅghaṃ sativinayaṃ yācati.**Because of his great clarity of memory, Dabba is asking the Sangha for resolution through recollection.*";
P_HTM[5021]="*Saṅgho āyasmato dabbassa mallaputtassa sativepullappattassa sativinayaṃ deti.**The Sangha grants resolution through recollection to Dabba.*";
P_HTM[5022]="*Yassāyasmato khamati āyasmato dabbassa mallaputtassa sativepullappattassa sativinayassa dānaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of granting resolution through recollection to Dabba should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[5023]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[5024]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[5025]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—**For the third time I speak on this matter.*";
P_HTM[5026]="*suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5027]="*Ime mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā anuddhaṃsenti.**These monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka are groundlessly charging Venerable Dabba the Mallian with failure in morality.*";
P_HTM[5028]="*Āyasmā dabbo mallaputto sativepullappatto saṅghaṃ sativinayaṃ yācati.**Because of his great clarity of memory, Dabba is asking the Sangha for resolution through recollection.*";
P_HTM[5029]="*Saṅgho āyasmato dabbassa mallaputtassa sativepullappattassa sativinayaṃ deti.**The Sangha grants resolution through recollection to Dabba.*";
P_HTM[5030]="*Yassāyasmato khamati āyasmato dabbassa mallaputtassa sativepullappattassa sativinayassa dānaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of granting resolution through recollection to Dabba should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[5031]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[5032]="*Dinno saṅghena āyasmato dabbassa mallaputtassa sativepullappattassa sativinayo.**Because of his great clarity of memory, the Sangha has granted resolution through recollection to Dabba the Mallian.*";
P_HTM[5033]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[5034]="*Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, dhammikāni sativinayassa dānāni.**“There are these five factors for the legitimate granting of resolution through recollection:*";
P_HTM[5035]="*Suddho hoti bhikkhu anāpattiko, anuvadanti ca naṃ, yācati ca, tassa saṅgho sativinayaṃ deti dhammena samaggena—**the monk is pure and free of offenses; he’s been accused; he asks for resolution through recollection; the Sangha grants him resolution through recollection; the legal procedure is legitimate and done by a unanimous assembly.”*";
P_HTM[5036]="*imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammikāni sativinayassa dānānī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5037]="*3. Amūḷhavinaya**3. Resolution because of past insanity*";
P_HTM[5038]="*Tena kho pana samayena gaggo bhikkhu ummattako hoti, cittavipariyāsakato.**At one time the monk Gagga was insane and suffering from psychosis.*";
P_HTM[5039]="*Tena ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ hoti bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**Because of that, he did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5040]="*Bhikkhū gaggaṃ bhikkhuṃ ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena ajjhāciṇṇena āpattiyā codenti—**Monks accused him of an offense, saying,*";
P_HTM[5041]="*“saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā”ti?**“Venerable, do you remember committing such-and-such an offense?”*";
P_HTM[5042]="*So evaṃ vadeti—* **";
P_HTM[5043]="*“ahaṃ kho, āvuso, ummattako ahosiṃ cittavipariyāsakato.**“I was insane and suffering from psychosis.*";
P_HTM[5044]="*Tena me ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**Because of that, I did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5045]="*Nāhaṃ taṃ sarāmi.**I don’t remember it;*";
P_HTM[5046]="*Mūḷhena me etaṃ katan”ti.**I did it because I was insane.”*";
P_HTM[5047]="*Evampi naṃ vuccamānā codenteva—**But they still accused him*";
P_HTM[5048]="*“saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā”ti?**in the same way.*";
P_HTM[5049]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[5050]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū gaggaṃ bhikkhuṃ ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena ajjhāciṇṇena āpattiyā codessanti—**“How can these monks keep on accusing Gagga*";
P_HTM[5051]="*‘saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5052]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**when he says*";
P_HTM[5053]="*‘ahaṃ kho, āvuso, ummattako ahosiṃ cittavipariyāsakato.**he was insane?”*";
P_HTM[5054]="*Tena me ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5055]="*Nāhaṃ taṃ sarāmi.* **";
P_HTM[5056]="*Mūḷhena me etaṃ katan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5057]="*Evampi naṃ vuccamānā codenteva—* **";
P_HTM[5058]="*‘saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5059]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha of monks gathered and questioned them:*";
P_HTM[5060]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave …pe…**He said, “Is it true, monks, that these monks are doing this?”*";
P_HTM[5061]="*saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5062]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[5063]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[5064]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho gaggassa bhikkhuno amūḷhassa amūḷhavinayaṃ detu.**“Well then, since he is no longer insane, grant resolution because of past insanity to the monk Gagga.*";
P_HTM[5065]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbo—**And it should be granted like this:*";
P_HTM[5066]="*tena, bhikkhave, gaggena bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā, ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā, vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā, ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā, añjaliṃ paggahetvā, evamassa vacanīyo—**The monk Gagga should approach the Sangha, put his upper robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and say:*";
P_HTM[5067]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, ummattako ahosiṃ cittavipariyāsakato.**‘Venerables, I have been insane and suffering from psychosis.*";
P_HTM[5068]="*Tena me ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**Because of that, I did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5069]="*Maṃ bhikkhū ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena ajjhāciṇṇena āpattiyā codenti—**Monks accused me of an offense,*";
P_HTM[5070]="*“saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā”ti?**“Venerable, do you remember committing such-and-such an offense?”*";
P_HTM[5071]="*Tyāhaṃ evaṃ vadāmi—**I replied,*";
P_HTM[5072]="*“ahaṃ kho, āvuso, ummattako ahosiṃ cittavipariyāsakato.**“I was insane and suffering from psychosis.*";
P_HTM[5073]="*Tena me ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**Because of that, I did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5074]="*Nāhaṃ taṃ sarāmi.**I don’t remember it;*";
P_HTM[5075]="*Mūḷhena me etaṃ katan”ti.**I did it because I was insane.”*";
P_HTM[5076]="*Evampi maṃ vuccamānā codenteva—**But they still accused me*";
P_HTM[5077]="*“saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā”ti?**in the same way.*";
P_HTM[5078]="*Sohaṃ, bhante, amūḷho saṅghaṃ amūḷhavinayaṃ yācāmī’ti.**Because I’m no longer insane, I ask the Sangha for resolution because of past insanity.’*";
P_HTM[5079]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbo.**And he should ask a second time,*";
P_HTM[5080]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbo—**and a third time:*";
P_HTM[5081]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, ummattako ahosiṃ cittavipariyāsakato.**‘Venerables, I have been insane and suffering from psychosis.*";
P_HTM[5082]="*Tena me ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**Because of that, I did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5083]="*Maṃ bhikkhū ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena ajjhāciṇṇena āpattiyā codenti—**Monks accused me of an offense,*";
P_HTM[5084]="*“saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā”ti?**“Venerable, do you remember committing such-and-such an offense?”*";
P_HTM[5085]="*Tyāhaṃ evaṃ vadāmi—**I replied,*";
P_HTM[5086]="*“ahaṃ kho, āvuso, ummattako ahosiṃ cittavipariyāsakato.**“I was insane and suffering from psychosis.*";
P_HTM[5087]="*Tena me ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**Because of that, I did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5088]="*Nāhaṃ taṃ sarāmi mūḷhena me etaṃ katan”ti.**I don’t remember it; I did it because I was insane.”*";
P_HTM[5089]="*Evampi maṃ vuccamānā codenteva—**But they still accused me*";
P_HTM[5090]="*“saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā”ti?**in the same way.*";
P_HTM[5091]="*Sohaṃ amūḷho tatiyampi, bhante, saṅghaṃ amūḷhavinayaṃ yācāmī’ti.**Because I’m no longer insane, for the third time I ask the Sangha for resolution because of past insanity.’*";
P_HTM[5092]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[5093]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5094]="*Ayaṃ gaggo bhikkhu ummattako ahosi cittavipariyāsakato.**The monk Gagga has been insane and suffering from psychosis.*";
P_HTM[5095]="*Tena ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**Because of that, he did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5096]="*Bhikkhū gaggaṃ bhikkhuṃ ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena ajjhāciṇṇena āpattiyā codenti—**Monks accused him of an offense,*";
P_HTM[5097]="*“saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā”ti?**“Venerable, do you remember committing such-and-such an offense?”*";
P_HTM[5098]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**He replied,*";
P_HTM[5099]="*“ahaṃ kho, āvuso, ummattako ahosiṃ cittavipariyāsakato.**“I was insane and suffering from psychosis.*";
P_HTM[5100]="*Tena me ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**Because of that, I did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5101]="*Nāhaṃ taṃ sarāmi, mūḷhena me etaṃ katan”ti.**I don’t remember it; I did it because I was insane.”*";
P_HTM[5102]="*Evampi naṃ vuccamānā codenteva—**But they still accused him*";
P_HTM[5103]="*“saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā”ti?**in the same way.*";
P_HTM[5104]="*So amūḷho saṅghaṃ amūḷhavinayaṃ yācati.**Because he is no longer insane, he is asking the Sangha for resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[5105]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho gaggassa bhikkhuno amūḷhassa amūḷhavinayaṃ dadeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should grant resolution because of past insanity to Gagga.*";
P_HTM[5106]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[5107]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5108]="*Ayaṃ gaggo bhikkhu ummattako ahosi cittavipariyāsakato.**The monk Gagga has been insane and suffering from psychosis.*";
P_HTM[5109]="*Tena ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**Because of that, he did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5110]="*Bhikkhū gaggaṃ bhikkhuṃ ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena ajjhāciṇṇena āpattiyā codenti—**Monks accused him of an offense,*";
P_HTM[5111]="*“saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā”ti?**“Venerable, do you remember committing such-and-such an offense?”*";
P_HTM[5112]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**He replied,*";
P_HTM[5113]="*“ahaṃ kho, āvuso, ummattako ahosiṃ cittavipariyāsakato.**“I was insane and suffering from psychosis.*";
P_HTM[5114]="*Tena me ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**Because of that, I did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5115]="*Nāhaṃ taṃ sarāmi mūḷhena me etaṃ katan”ti.**I don’t remember it; I did it because I was insane.”*";
P_HTM[5116]="*Evampi naṃ vuccamānā codenteva—**But they still accused him*";
P_HTM[5117]="*“saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā”ti?**in the same way.*";
P_HTM[5118]="*So amūḷho saṅghaṃ amūḷhavinayaṃ yācati.**Because he is no longer insane, he is asking the Sangha for resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[5119]="*Saṅgho gaggassa bhikkhuno amūḷhassa amūḷhavinayaṃ deti.**The Sangha grants resolution because of past insanity to Gagga.*";
P_HTM[5120]="*Yassāyasmato khamati gaggassa bhikkhuno amūḷhassa amūḷhavinayassa dānaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of granting resolution because of past insanity to Gagga should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[5121]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[5122]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[5123]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe….**For the third time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[5124]="*Dinno saṅghena gaggassa bhikkhuno amūḷhassa amūḷhavinayo.**Since he is no longer insane, the Sangha has granted resolution because of past insanity to the monk Gagga.*";
P_HTM[5125]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[5126]="*Tīṇimāni, bhikkhave, adhammikāni amūḷhavinayassa dānāni, tīṇi dhammikāni.**There are three illegitimate and three legitimate grantings of resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[5127]="*Katamāni tīṇi adhammikāni amūḷhavinayassa dānāni?**What are the three illegitimate grantings of resolution because of past insanity?*";
P_HTM[5128]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āpattiṃ āpanno hoti.**It may be that a monk has committed an offense.*";
P_HTM[5129]="*Tamenaṃ codeti saṅgho vā, sambahulā vā, ekapuggalo vā—**The Sangha, several monks, or a single monk accuses him, saying,*";
P_HTM[5130]="*‘saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā’ti?**‘Venerable, do you remember committing such-and-such an offense?’*";
P_HTM[5131]="*So saramānova evaṃ vadeti—**Although he remembers, he says*";
P_HTM[5132]="*‘na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, sarāmi evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā’ti.**he doesn’t.*";
P_HTM[5133]="*Tassa saṅgho amūḷhavinayaṃ deti.**If the Sangha grants him resolution because of past insanity,*";
P_HTM[5134]="*Adhammikaṃ amūḷhavinayassa dānaṃ.**then that granting is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[5135]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āpattiṃ āpanno hoti.**It may be that a monk has committed an offense.*";
P_HTM[5136]="*Tamenaṃ codeti saṅgho vā, sambahulā vā, ekapuggalo vā—**The Sangha, several monks, or a single monk accuses him, saying,*";
P_HTM[5137]="*‘saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā’ti?**‘Venerable, do you remember committing such-and-such an offense?’*";
P_HTM[5138]="*So saramānova evaṃ vadeti—**Although he remembers, he says,*";
P_HTM[5139]="*‘sarāmi kho ahaṃ, āvuso, yathāsupinantenā’ti.**‘I remember as if in a dream.’*";
P_HTM[5140]="*Tassa saṅgho amūḷhavinayaṃ deti.**If the Sangha grants him resolution because of past insanity,*";
P_HTM[5141]="*Adhammikaṃ amūḷhavinayassa dānaṃ.**then that granting is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[5142]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āpattiṃ āpanno hoti.**It may be that a monk has committed an offense.*";
P_HTM[5143]="*Tamenaṃ codeti saṅgho vā, sambahulā vā, ekapuggalo vā—**The Sangha, several monks, or a single monk accuses him, saying,*";
P_HTM[5144]="*‘saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā’ti?**‘Venerable, do you remember committing such-and-such an offense?’*";
P_HTM[5145]="*So anummattako ummattakālayaṃ karoti—**Although he is sane, he acts insane, saying,*";
P_HTM[5146]="*‘ahampi kho evaṃ karomi.**‘I do this,*";
P_HTM[5147]="*Tumhepi evaṃ karotha.**and so do you.*";
P_HTM[5148]="*Mayhampi etaṃ kappati.**This is allowable for me,*";
P_HTM[5149]="*Tumhākampetaṃ kappatī’ti.**and also for you.’*";
P_HTM[5150]="*Tassa saṅgho amūḷhavinayaṃ deti.**If the Sangha grants him resolution because of past insanity,*";
P_HTM[5151]="*Adhammikaṃ amūḷhavinayassa dānaṃ.**then that granting is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[5152]="*Imāni tīṇi adhammikāni amūḷhavinayassa dānāni.**These are the three illegitimate grantings of resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[5153]="*Katamāni tīṇi dhammikāni amūḷhavinayassa dānāni?**What are the three legitimate grantings of resolution because of past insanity?*";
P_HTM[5154]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ummattako hoti cittavipariyāsakato.**It may be that a monk has been insane and suffering from psychosis.*";
P_HTM[5155]="*Tena ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ hoti bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**Because of that, he did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5156]="*Tamenaṃ codeti saṅgho vā, sambahulā vā, ekapuggalo vā—**The Sangha, several monks, or a single monk accuses him, saying,*";
P_HTM[5157]="*‘saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā’ti?**‘Venerable, do you remember committing such-and-such an offense?’*";
P_HTM[5158]="*So assaramānova evaṃ vadeti—**Not remembering, he says*";
P_HTM[5159]="*‘na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, sarāmi evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā’ti.**he doesn’t.*";
P_HTM[5160]="*Tassa saṅgho amūḷhavinayaṃ deti.**If the Sangha grants him resolution because of past insanity,*";
P_HTM[5161]="*Dhammikaṃ amūḷhavinayassa dānaṃ.**then that granting is legitimate.*";
P_HTM[5162]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ummattako hoti cittavipariyāsakato.**It may be that a monk has been insane and suffering from psychosis.*";
P_HTM[5163]="*Tena ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ hoti bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**Because of that, he did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5164]="*Tamenaṃ codeti saṅgho vā, sambahulā vā, ekapuggalo vā—**The Sangha, several monks, or a single monk accuses him, saying,*";
P_HTM[5165]="*‘saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā’ti?**‘Venerable, do you remember committing such-and-such an offense?’*";
P_HTM[5166]="*So assaramānova evaṃ vadeti—**Not remembering, he says,*";
P_HTM[5167]="*‘sarāmi kho ahaṃ, āvuso, yathāsupinantenā’ti.**‘I remember as if in a dream.’*";
P_HTM[5168]="*Tassa saṅgho amūḷhavinayaṃ deti.**If the Sangha grants him resolution because of past insanity,*";
P_HTM[5169]="*Dhammikaṃ amūḷhavinayassa dānaṃ.**then that granting is legitimate.*";
P_HTM[5170]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ummattako hoti cittavipariyāsakato.**It may be that a monk has been insane and suffering from psychosis.*";
P_HTM[5171]="*Tena ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ hoti bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**Because of that, he did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5172]="*Tamenaṃ codeti saṅgho vā, sambahulā vā, ekapuggalo vā—**The Sangha, several monks, or a single monk accuses him, saying,*";
P_HTM[5173]="*‘saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā’ti?**‘Venerable, do you remember committing such-and-such an offense?’*";
P_HTM[5174]="*So ummattako ummattakālayaṃ karoti—**Being insane, he acts insane, saying,*";
P_HTM[5175]="*‘ahampi evaṃ karomi.**‘I do this,*";
P_HTM[5176]="*Tumhepi evaṃ karotha.**and so do you.*";
P_HTM[5177]="*Mayhampi etaṃ kappati.**This is allowable for me,*";
P_HTM[5178]="*Tumhākampetaṃ kappatī’ti.**and also for you.’*";
P_HTM[5179]="*Tassa saṅgho amūḷhavinayaṃ deti.**If the Sangha grants him resolution because of past insanity,*";
P_HTM[5180]="*Dhammikaṃ amūḷhavinayassa dānaṃ.**then that granting is legitimate.*";
P_HTM[5181]="*Imāni tīṇi dhammikāni amūḷhavinayassa dānānī”ti.**These are the three legitimate grantings of resolution because of past insanity.”*";
P_HTM[5182]="*4. Paṭiññātakaraṇa**4. Acting according to what has been admitted*";
P_HTM[5183]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū appaṭiññāya bhikkhūnaṃ kammāni karonti—**At one time the monks from the group of six did legal procedures—*";
P_HTM[5184]="*tajjanīyampi, niyassampi, pabbājanīyampi, paṭisāraṇīyampi, ukkhepanīyampi.**condemnation, demotion, banishment, reconciliation, and ejection—against other monks without their admission.*";
P_HTM[5185]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[5186]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū appaṭiññāya bhikkhūnaṃ kammāni karissanti—**“How can the monks from the group of six do this?”*";
P_HTM[5187]="*tajjanīyampi, niyassampi, pabbājanīyampi, paṭisāraṇīyampi, ukkhepanīyampī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5188]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha of monks gathered and questioned them:*";
P_HTM[5189]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave …pe…**“Is it true, monks, that the monks from the group of six are doing this?”*";
P_HTM[5190]="*“saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5191]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[5192]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[5193]="*“na, bhikkhave, appaṭiññāya bhikkhūnaṃ kammaṃ kātabbaṃ—**“You should not do legal procedures—*";
P_HTM[5194]="*tajjanīyaṃ vā, niyassaṃ vā, pabbājanīyaṃ vā, paṭisāraṇīyaṃ vā, ukkhepanīyaṃ vā.**condemnation, demotion, banishment, reconciliation, or ejection—against monks without their admission.*";
P_HTM[5195]="*Yo kareyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5196]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, adhammikaṃ hoti paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ, evaṃ dhammikaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5197]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, adhammikaṃ hoti paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ?**“And how is acting according to what has been admitted illegitimate?*";
P_HTM[5198]="*Bhikkhu pārājikaṃ ajjhāpanno hoti.**It may be that a monk has committed an offense entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[5199]="*Tamenaṃ codeti saṅgho vā, sambahulā vā, ekapuggalo vā—**The Sangha, several monks, or a single monk accuses him, saying,*";
P_HTM[5200]="*‘pārājikaṃ āyasmā ajjhāpanno’ti?**‘Venerable, you have committed an offense entailing expulsion.’*";
P_HTM[5201]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**He says,*";
P_HTM[5202]="*‘na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, pārājikaṃ ajjhāpanno, saṅghādisesaṃ ajjhāpanno’ti.**‘I haven’t committed an offense entailing expulsion, but one entailing suspension.’*";
P_HTM[5203]="*Taṃ saṅgho saṅghādisesena kāreti.**If the Sangha makes him act according to an offense entailing suspension,*";
P_HTM[5204]="*Adhammikaṃ paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ.**then that acting according to what has been admitted is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[5205]="*Bhikkhu pārājikaṃ ajjhāpanno hoti.**It may be that a monk has committed an offense entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[5206]="*Tamenaṃ codeti saṅgho vā, sambahulā vā, ekapuggalo vā—**The Sangha, several monks, or a single monk accuses him, saying,*";
P_HTM[5207]="*‘pārājikaṃ āyasmā ajjhāpanno’ti?**‘Venerable, you have committed an offense entailing expulsion.’*";
P_HTM[5208]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**He says,*";
P_HTM[5209]="*‘na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, pārājikaṃ ajjhāpanno, thullaccayaṃ …pe…**‘I haven’t committed an offense entailing expulsion, but a serious offense …*";
P_HTM[5210]="*pācittiyaṃ …pe…**but an offense entailing confession …*";
P_HTM[5211]="*pāṭidesanīyaṃ …pe…**but an offense entailing acknowledgment …*";
P_HTM[5212]="*dukkaṭaṃ …pe…**but an offense of wrong conduct …*";
P_HTM[5213]="*dubbhāsitaṃ ajjhāpanno’ti.**but an offense of wrong speech.’*";
P_HTM[5214]="*Taṃ saṅgho dubbhāsitena kāreti.**If the Sangha makes him act according to an offense of wrong speech,*";
P_HTM[5215]="*Adhammikaṃ paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ.**then that acting according to what has been admitted is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[5216]="*Bhikkhu saṅghādisesaṃ …pe…**It may be that a monk has committed an offense entailing suspension …*";
P_HTM[5217]="*thullaccayaṃ …pe…**a serious offense …*";
P_HTM[5218]="*pācittiyaṃ …pe…**an offense entailing confession …*";
P_HTM[5219]="*pāṭidesanīyaṃ …pe…**an offense entailing acknowledgment …*";
P_HTM[5220]="*dukkaṭaṃ …pe…**an offense of wrong conduct …*";
P_HTM[5221]="*dubbhāsitaṃ ajjhāpanno hoti.**an offense of wrong speech.*";
P_HTM[5222]="*Tamenaṃ codeti saṅgho vā, sambahulā vā, ekapuggalo vā—**The Sangha, several monks, or a single monk accuses him, saying,*";
P_HTM[5223]="*‘dubbhāsitaṃ āyasmā ajjhāpanno’ti?**‘Venerable, you have committed an offense of wrong speech.’*";
