P_HTM[5229]="*Tamenaṃ codeti saṅgho vā, sambahulā vā, ekapuggalo vā—**The Sangha, several monks, or a single monk accuses him, saying,*";
P_HTM[5230]="*‘dubbhāsitaṃ āyasmā ajjhāpanno’ti?**‘Venerable, you have committed an offense of wrong speech.’*";
P_HTM[5231]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**He says,*";
P_HTM[5232]="*‘na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, dubbhāsitaṃ ajjhāpanno, saṅghādisesaṃ …pe…**‘I haven’t committed an offense of wrong speech, but an offense entailing suspension …*";
P_HTM[5233]="*thullaccayaṃ …pe…**but a serious offense …*";
P_HTM[5234]="*pācittiyaṃ …pe…**but an offense entailing confession …*";
P_HTM[5235]="*pāṭidesanīyaṃ …pe…**but an offense entailing acknowledgment …*";
P_HTM[5236]="*dukkaṭaṃ ajjhāpanno’ti.**but an offense of wrong conduct.’*";
P_HTM[5237]="*Taṃ saṅgho dukkaṭena kāreti.**If the Sangha makes him act according to an offense of wrong conduct,*";
P_HTM[5238]="*Adhammikaṃ paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ.**then that acting according to what has been admitted is illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[5239]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, adhammikaṃ hoti paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5240]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, dhammikaṃ hoti paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ?**“And how is acting according to what has been admitted legitimate?*";
P_HTM[5241]="*Bhikkhu pārājikaṃ ajjhāpanno hoti.**It may be that a monk has committed an offense entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[5242]="*Tamenaṃ codeti saṅgho vā, sambahulā vā, ekapuggalo vā—**The Sangha, several monks, or a single monk accuses him, saying*";
P_HTM[5243]="*‘pārājikaṃ āyasmā ajjhāpanno’ti?**‘Venerable, you have committed an offense entailing expulsion.’*";
P_HTM[5244]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**He says,*";
P_HTM[5245]="*‘āma, āvuso, pārājikaṃ ajjhāpanno’ti.**‘Yes, I have committed an offense entailing expulsion.’*";
P_HTM[5246]="*Taṃ saṅgho pārājikena kāreti.**If the Sangha makes him act according to an offense entailing expulsion,*";
P_HTM[5247]="*Dhammikaṃ paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ.**then that acting according to what has been admitted is legitimate.*";
P_HTM[5248]="*Bhikkhu saṅghādisesaṃ …pe…**It may be that a monk has committed an offense entailing suspension …*";
P_HTM[5249]="*thullaccayaṃ …pe…**a serious offense …*";
P_HTM[5250]="*pācittiyaṃ …pe…**an offense entailing confession …*";
P_HTM[5251]="*pāṭidesanīyaṃ …pe…**an offense entailing acknowledgment …*";
P_HTM[5252]="*dukkaṭaṃ …pe…**an offense of wrong conduct …*";
P_HTM[5253]="*dubbhāsitaṃ ajjhāpanno hoti.**an offense of wrong speech.*";
P_HTM[5254]="*Tamenaṃ codeti saṅgho vā, sambahulā vā, ekapuggalo vā—**The Sangha, several monks, or a single monk accuses him, saying,*";
P_HTM[5255]="*‘dubbhāsitaṃ āyasmā ajjhāpanno’ti?**‘Venerable, you have committed an offense of wrong speech.’*";
P_HTM[5256]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**He says,*";
P_HTM[5257]="*‘āma, āvuso, dubbhāsitaṃ ajjhāpanno’ti.**‘Yes, I have committed an offense of wrong speech.’*";
P_HTM[5258]="*Taṃ saṅgho dubbhāsitena kāreti.**If the Sangha makes him act according to an offense wrong speech,*";
P_HTM[5259]="*Dhammikaṃ paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ.**then that acting according to what has been admitted is legitimate.”*";
P_HTM[5260]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dhammikaṃ hoti paṭiññātakaraṇan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5261]="*5. Yebhuyyasikā**5. Majority decision*";
P_HTM[5262]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū saṅghamajjhe bhaṇḍanajātā kalahajātā vivādāpannā aññamaññaṃ mukhasattīhi vitudantā viharanti, na sakkonti taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**At one time the monks were arguing and disputing in the midst of the Sangha, attacking one another verbally, and they were unable to resolve that legal issue.*";
P_HTM[5263]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[5264]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, evarūpaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ yebhuyyasikāya vūpasametuṃ.**“I allow you to resolve such legal issues by majority decision.*";
P_HTM[5265]="*Pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu salākaggāhāpako sammannitabbo—**You should appoint a monk who has five qualities as the manager of the vote:*";
P_HTM[5266]="*yo na chandāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na dosāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na mohāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na bhayāgatiṃ gaccheyya, gahitāgahitañca jāneyya.**one who isn’t swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear, and who knows who has and has not voted.*";
P_HTM[5267]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sammannitabbo.**And he should be appointed like this.*";
P_HTM[5268]="*Paṭhamaṃ bhikkhu yācitabbo, yācitvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**First a monk should be asked, and then a competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[5269]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5270]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ salākaggāhāpakaṃ sammanneyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should appoint monk so-and-so as the manager of the vote.*";
P_HTM[5271]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[5272]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5273]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ salākaggāhāpakaṃ sammannati.**The Sangha appoints monk so-and-so as the manager of the vote.*";
P_HTM[5274]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno salākaggāhāpakassa sammuti, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of appointing monk so-and-so as the manager of the vote should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[5275]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[5276]="*Sammato saṅghena itthannāmo bhikkhu salākaggāhāpako.**The Sangha has appointed monk so-and-so as the manager of the vote.*";
P_HTM[5277]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[5278]="*Dasayime, bhikkhave, adhammikā salākaggāhā, dasa dhammikā.**“There are ten reasons why a vote is illegitimate:*";
P_HTM[5279]="*Katame dasa adhammikā salākaggāhā?* **";
P_HTM[5280]="*Oramattakañca adhikaraṇaṃ hoti, na ca gatigataṃ hoti, na ca saritasāritaṃ hoti, jānāti adhammavādī bahutarāti, appeva nāma adhammavādī bahutarā assūti, jānāti saṅgho bhijjissatīti, appeva nāma saṅgho bhijjeyyāti, adhammena gaṇhanti, vaggā gaṇhanti, na ca yathādiṭṭhiyā gaṇhanti—**it is only a minor legal issue; the full process for settling it hasn’t run its course; they haven’t tried to remember offenses and remind about offenses; the manager knows that those who speak contrary to the Teaching are in the majority; the manager expects that those who speak contrary to the Teaching will be in the majority; the manager knows that the Sangha will split; the manager expects that the Sangha will be split; they vote illegitimately; they vote with an incomplete assembly; they don’t vote according to their own views.*";
P_HTM[5281]="*ime dasa adhammikā salākaggāhā.* **";
P_HTM[5282]="*Katame dasa dhammikā salākaggāhā?**There are ten reasons why a vote is legitimate:*";
P_HTM[5283]="*Na ca oramattakaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ hoti, gatigatañca hoti, saritasāritañca hoti, jānāti dhammavādī bahutarāti, appeva nāma dhammavādī bahutarā assūti, jānāti saṅgho na bhijjissatīti, appeva nāma saṅgho na bhijjeyyāti, dhammena gaṇhanti, samaggā gaṇhanti, yathādiṭṭhiyā ca gaṇhanti—**it’s not a minor legal issue; the full process for settling it has run its course; they have tried to remember offenses and remind about offenses; the manager knows that those who speak in accordance with the Teaching are in the majority; the manager expects that those who speak in accordance with the Teaching will be in the majority; the manager knows that the Sangha will not split; the manager expects that the Sangha will not be split; they vote legitimately; they vote with a complete assembly; they vote according to their own views.”*";
P_HTM[5284]="*ime dasa dhammikā salākaggāhā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5285]="*6. Tassapāpiyasikā**6. Further penalty*";
P_HTM[5286]="*Tena kho pana samayena upavāḷo bhikkhu saṅghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjiyamāno avajānitvā paṭijānāti, paṭijānitvā avajānāti, aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati, sampajānamusā bhāsati.**On one occasion, while the monk Upavāḷa was being examined in the midst of the Sangha about an offense, he asserted things after denying them, denied things after asserting them, evaded the issue, and lied.*";
P_HTM[5287]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[5288]="*“kathañhi nāma upavāḷo bhikkhu saṅghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjiyamāno avajānitvā paṭijānissati, paṭijānitvā avajānissati, aññenaññaṃ paṭicarissati, sampajānamusā bhāsissatī”ti.**“How could the monk Upavāḷa act like this?”*";
P_HTM[5289]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha of monks gathered and questioned them:*";
P_HTM[5290]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave …pe…**“Is it true, monks, that the monk Upavāḷa is acting like this?”*";
P_HTM[5291]="*“saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5292]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing him …*";
P_HTM[5293]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[5294]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho upavāḷassa bhikkhuno tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ karotu.**“Well then, the Sangha should do a legal procedure of further penalty against the monk Upavāḷa.*";
P_HTM[5295]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, kātabbaṃ.**And it should be done like this.*";
P_HTM[5296]="*Paṭhamaṃ upavāḷo bhikkhu codetabbo, codetvā sāretabbo, sāretvā āpattiṃ āropetabbo, āpattiṃ āropetvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**First you should accuse the monk Upavāḷa. He should then be reminded of what he’s done, before he is charged with an offense. A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[5297]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5298]="*Ayaṃ upavāḷo bhikkhu saṅghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjiyamāno avajānitvā paṭijānāti, paṭijānitvā avajānāti, aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati, sampajānamusā bhāsati.**The monk Upavāḷa, while being examined in the midst of the Sangha about an offense, asserted things after denying them, denied things after asserting them, evaded the issue, and lied.*";
P_HTM[5299]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho upavāḷassa bhikkhuno tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ kareyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should do a legal procedure of further penalty against him.*";
P_HTM[5300]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[5301]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5302]="*Ayaṃ upavāḷo bhikkhu saṅghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjiyamāno avajānitvā paṭijānāti, paṭijānitvā avajānāti, aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati, sampajānamusā bhāsati.**The monk Upavāḷa, while being examined in the midst of the Sangha about an offense, asserted things after denying them, denied things after asserting them, evaded the issue, and lied.*";
P_HTM[5303]="*Saṅgho upavāḷassa bhikkhuno tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ karoti.**The Sangha should do a legal procedure of further penalty against him.*";
P_HTM[5304]="*Yassāyasmato khamati upavāḷassa bhikkhuno tassapāpiyasikākammassa karaṇaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of doing a legal procedure of further penalty against him should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[5305]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[5306]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[5307]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe….**For the third time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[5308]="*Kataṃ saṅghena upavāḷassa bhikkhuno tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of further penalty against the monk Upavāḷa.*";
P_HTM[5309]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[5310]="*Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, dhammikāni tassapāpiyasikākammassa karaṇāni.**There are these five factors of a legitimate legal procedure of further penalty:*";
P_HTM[5311]="*Asuci ca hoti, alajjī ca, sānuvādo ca, tassa saṅgho tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ karoti dhammena, samaggena—**the subject of the procedure is impure; he is shameless; he’s been accused; the procedure is legitimate; the procedure is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[5312]="*imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammikāni tassapāpiyasikākammassa karaṇāni.* **";
P_HTM[5313]="*6.1. Adhammakammadvādasaka**6.1 The group of twelve on illegitimate legal procedures*";
P_HTM[5314]="*Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgataṃ tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.**“When a legal procedure of further penalty has three qualities, it is illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[5315]="*Asammukhā kataṃ hoti, appaṭipucchākataṃ hoti, appaṭiññāya kataṃ hoti …pe…**it is done in the absence of the accused, it is done without questioning the accused, it is done without the admission of the accused.*";
P_HTM[5316]="*When a procedure of further penalty has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done against one who hasn’t committed any offense, it is done against one who has committed an offense that isn’t clearable by confession, it is done against one who has confessed their offense.* **";
P_HTM[5317]="*When a procedure of further penalty has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having accused the person of their offense, it is done without having reminded the person of their offense, it is done without having charged the person with their offense.* **";
P_HTM[5318]="*“When a procedure of further penalty has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done in the absence of the accused, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.* **";
P_HTM[5319]="*When a procedure of further penalty has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without questioning the accused, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.* **";
P_HTM[5320]="*When a procedure of further penalty has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without the admission of the accused, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.* **";
P_HTM[5321]="*“When a procedure of further penalty has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done against one who hasn’t committed any offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.* **";
P_HTM[5322]="*When a procedure of further penalty has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done against one who has committed an offense that isn’t clearable by confession, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.* **";
P_HTM[5323]="*When a procedure of further penalty has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done against one who has confessed their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.* **";
P_HTM[5324]="*“When a procedure of further penalty has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having accused the person of their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.* **";
P_HTM[5325]="*When a procedure of further penalty has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having reminded the person of their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.* **";
P_HTM[5326]="*… adhammena kataṃ hoti, vaggena kataṃ hoti—**When a procedure of further penalty has another three qualities, it is also illegitimate, contrary to the Monastic Law, and not properly resolved: it is done without having charged the person with their offense, it is done illegitimately, it is done by an incomplete assembly.*";
P_HTM[5327]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ adhammakammañca hoti, avinayakammañca, duvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[5328]="*6.2. Dhammakammadvādasaka**6.2 The group of twelve on legitimate legal procedures*";
P_HTM[5329]="*Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgataṃ tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.**“When a legal procedure of further penalty has three qualities, it is legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved:*";
P_HTM[5330]="*Sammukhā kataṃ hoti, paṭipucchākataṃ hoti, paṭiññāya kataṃ hoti …pe…**it is done in the presence of the accused, it is done with the questioning of the accused, it is done with the admission of the accused.*";
P_HTM[5331]="*… dhammena kataṃ hoti, samaggena kataṃ hoti—**When a procedure of further penalty has another three qualities, it is also legitimate, in accordance with the Monastic Law, and properly resolved: it is done after having charged the person with their offense, it is done legitimately, it is done by a unanimous assembly.*";
P_HTM[5332]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgataṃ tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ dhammakammañca hoti, vinayakammañca, suvūpasantañca.* **";
P_HTM[5333]="*6.3. Ākaṅkhamānachakka**6.3 The group of six on wishing*";
P_HTM[5334]="*Tīhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ kareyya.**“When a monk has three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a legal procedure of further penalty against him:*";
P_HTM[5335]="*Bhaṇḍanakārako hoti kalahakārako vivādakārako bhassakārako saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako;**he is quarrelsome, argumentative, and a creator of legal issues in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[5336]="*bālo hoti abyatto āpattibahulo anapadāno;**he is ignorant, incompetent, often committing offenses, incapable of determining whether he’s committed an offense;*";
P_HTM[5337]="*gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi—**he is constantly and improperly socializing with householders.*";
P_HTM[5338]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[5339]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ kareyya.**When a monk has another three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of further penalty against him:*";
P_HTM[5340]="*Adhisīle sīlavipanno hoti, ajjhācāre ācāravipanno hoti, atidiṭṭhiyā diṭṭhivipanno hoti—**he has failed in the higher morality; he has failed in conduct; he has failed in view.*";
P_HTM[5341]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave …pe….* **";
P_HTM[5342]="*Aparehipi, bhikkhave …pe…**When a monk has another three qualities, the Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of further penalty against him:*";
P_HTM[5343]="*buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—**he disparages the Buddha; he disparages the Teaching; he disparages the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[5344]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhaṅgehi samannāgatassa bhikkhuno ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[5345]="*Tiṇṇaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ kareyya.**The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of further penalty against three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[5346]="*Eko bhaṇḍanakārako hoti …pe…**those who are quarrelsome, argumentative,*";
P_HTM[5347]="*saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako;**and creators of legal issues in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[5348]="*eko bālo hoti abyatto āpattibahulo anapadāno;**those who are ignorant, incompetent, often committing offenses, incapable of determining whether they have committed an offense;*";
P_HTM[5349]="*eko gihisaṃsaṭṭho viharati ananulomikehi gihisaṃsaggehi—**those who are constantly and improperly socializing with householders.*";
P_HTM[5350]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[5351]="*Aparesampi, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ kareyya.**The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of further penalty against another three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[5352]="*Eko adhisīle sīlavipanno hoti, eko ajjhācāre ācāravipanno hoti, eko atidiṭṭhiyā diṭṭhivipanno hoti—**those who have failed in the higher morality; those who have failed in the higher conduct; those who have failed in view.*";
P_HTM[5353]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave …pe….* **";
P_HTM[5354]="*Aparesampi, bhikkhave …pe…**The Sangha may, if it wishes, do a procedure of further penalty against another three kinds of monks:*";
P_HTM[5355]="*eko buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, eko dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, eko saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—**those who disparage the Buddha; those who disparage the Teaching; those who disparage the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[5356]="*imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tiṇṇaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ ākaṅkhamāno saṅgho tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[5357]="*6.4. Aṭṭhārasavatta**6.4 The eighteen kinds of conduct*";
P_HTM[5358]="*Tassapāpiyasikākammakatena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā sammā vattitabbaṃ.**“A monk who has had a legal procedure of further penalty done against himself should conduct himself properly.*";
P_HTM[5359]="*Tatrāyaṃ sammāvattanā—**This is the proper conduct:*";
P_HTM[5360]="*Na upasampādetabbaṃ,**He should not give the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[5361]="*na nissayo dātabbo,**He should not give formal support.*";
P_HTM[5362]="*na sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo,**He should not have a novice monk attend on him.*";
P_HTM[5363]="*na bhikkhunovādakasammuti sāditabbā,**He should not accept being appointed as an instructor of the nuns.*";
P_HTM[5364]="*sammatenapi bhikkhuniyo na ovaditabbā …pe…**Even if appointed, he should not instruct the nuns.*";
P_HTM[5365]="*na bhikkhūhi sampayojetabban”ti.**He should not associate inappropriately with other monks.”*";
P_HTM[5366]="*Atha kho saṅgho upavāḷassa bhikkhuno tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ akāsi.**The Sangha then did a legal procedure of further penalty against the monk Upavāḷa.*";
P_HTM[5367]="*7. Tiṇavatthāraka**7. Covering over as if with grass*";
P_HTM[5368]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ viharataṃ bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ hoti bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**At one time, while the monks were arguing and disputing, they did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5369]="*Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**They considered this and thought,*";
P_HTM[5370]="*“amhākaṃ kho bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ viharataṃ bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5371]="*Sace mayaṃ imāhi āpattīhi aññamaññaṃ kāressāma, siyāpi taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ kakkhaḷattāya vāḷattāya bhedāya saṃvatteyya.**“If we deal with one another for these offenses, this legal issue might lead to harshness, nastiness, and schism.*";
P_HTM[5372]="*Kathaṃ nu kho amhehi paṭipajjitabban”ti?**So what should we do now?”*";
P_HTM[5373]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[5374]="*“Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ viharataṃ bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ hoti bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**“It may be, monks, that monks who are arguing and disputing do and say many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5375]="*Tatra ce bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ hoti—**If they consider this and think,*";
P_HTM[5376]="*‘amhākaṃ kho bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ viharataṃ bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[5377]="*sace mayaṃ imāhi āpattīhi aññamaññaṃ kāressāma, siyāpi taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ kakkhaḷattāya vāḷattāya bhedāya saṃvatteyyā’ti, anujānāmi, bhikkhave, evarūpaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ tiṇavatthārakena vūpasametuṃ.**‘If we deal with one another for these offenses, this legal issue might lead to harshness, nastiness, and schism,’ then I allow you to resolve this legal issue by covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[5378]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, vūpasametabbaṃ.**And it should be resolved like this.*";
P_HTM[5379]="*Sabbeheva ekajjhaṃ sannipatitabbaṃ, sannipatitvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**Everyone should gather in one place. A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[5380]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5381]="*Amhākaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ viharataṃ bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**While we were arguing and disputing, we did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5382]="*Sace mayaṃ imāhi āpattīhi aññamaññaṃ kāressāma, siyāpi taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ kakkhaḷattāya vāḷattāya bhedāya saṃvatteyya.**If we deal with one another for these offenses, this legal issue might lead to harshness, nastiness, and schism.*";
P_HTM[5383]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ tiṇavatthārakena vūpasameyya, ṭhapetvā thullavajjaṃ, ṭhapetvā gihippaṭisaṃyuttan’ti.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should resolve this legal issue by covering over as if with grass, except for heavy offenses and offenses connected with householders.’*";
P_HTM[5384]="*Ekatopakkhikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena sako pakkho ñāpetabbo—**The monks belonging to one side should be informed by a competent and capable monk belonging to their own side:*";
P_HTM[5385]="*‘Suṇantu me āyasmantā.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask you to listen.*";
P_HTM[5386]="*Amhākaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ viharataṃ bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**While we were arguing and disputing, we did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5387]="*Sace mayaṃ imāhi āpattīhi aññamaññaṃ kāressāma, siyāpi taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ kakkhaḷattāya vāḷattāya bhedāya saṃvatteyya.**If we deal with one another for these offenses, this legal issue might lead to harshness, nastiness, and schism.*";
P_HTM[5388]="*Yadāyasmantānaṃ pattakallaṃ, ahaṃ yā ceva āyasmantānaṃ āpatti, yā ca attano āpatti, āyasmantānañceva atthāya, attano ca atthāya, saṅghamajjhe tiṇavatthārakena deseyyaṃ, ṭhapetvā thullavajjaṃ, ṭhapetvā gihippaṭisaṃyuttan’ti.**If it seems appropriate to the venerables, then for your benefit and for my own, I will confess in the midst of the Sangha both your and my own offenses by covering over as if with grass, except for heavy offenses and offenses connected with householders.’*";
P_HTM[5389]="*Athāparesaṃ ekatopakkhikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena sako pakkho ñāpetabbo—**The monks belonging to the other side should be informed by a competent and capable monk belonging to their own side:*";
P_HTM[5390]="*‘Suṇantu me āyasmantā.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask you to listen.*";
P_HTM[5391]="*Amhākaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ viharataṃ bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**While we were arguing and disputing, we did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5392]="*Sace mayaṃ imāhi āpattīhi aññamaññaṃ kāressāma, siyāpi taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ kakkhaḷattāya vāḷattāya bhedāya saṃvatteyya.**If we deal with one another for these offenses, this legal issue might lead to harshness, nastiness, and schism.*";
P_HTM[5393]="*Yadāyasmantānaṃ pattakallaṃ, ahaṃ yā ceva āyasmantānaṃ āpatti, yā ca attano āpatti, āyasmantānañceva atthāya, attano ca atthāya, saṅghamajjhe tiṇavatthārakena deseyyaṃ, ṭhapetvā thullavajjaṃ, ṭhapetvā gihippaṭisaṃyuttan’ti.**If it seems appropriate to the venerables, then for your benefit and for my own, I will confess in the midst of the Sangha both your and my own offenses by covering over as if with grass, except for heavy offenses and offenses connected with householders.’*";
P_HTM[5394]="*Athāparesaṃ ekatopakkhikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**“A competent and capable monk belonging to one side should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[5395]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5396]="*Amhākaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ viharataṃ bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**While we were arguing and disputing, we did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5397]="*Sace mayaṃ imāhi āpattīhi aññamaññaṃ kāressāma, siyāpi taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ kakkhaḷattāya vāḷattāya bhedāya saṃvatteyya.**If we deal with one another for these offenses, this legal issue might lead to harshness, nastiness, and schism.*";
P_HTM[5398]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, ahaṃ yā ceva imesaṃ āyasmantānaṃ āpatti, yā ca attano āpatti, imesañceva āyasmantānaṃ atthāya, attano ca atthāya, saṅghamajjhe tiṇavatthārakena deseyyaṃ, ṭhapetvā thullavajjaṃ, ṭhapetvā gihippaṭisaṃyuttaṃ.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, then for the benefit of these venerables and myself, I will confess in the midst of the Sangha both their and my own offenses by covering over as if with grass, except for heavy offenses and offenses connected with householders.*";
P_HTM[5399]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[5400]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5401]="*Amhākaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ viharataṃ bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**While we were arguing and disputing, we did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5402]="*Sace mayaṃ imāhi āpattīhi aññamaññaṃ kāressāma, siyāpi taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ kakkhaḷattāya vāḷattāya bhedāya saṃvatteyya.**If we deal with one another for these offenses, this legal issue might lead to harshness, nastiness, and schism.*";
P_HTM[5403]="*Ahaṃ yā ceva imesaṃ āyasmantānaṃ āpatti, yā ca attano āpatti, imesañceva āyasmantānaṃ atthāya, attano ca atthāya, saṅghamajjhe tiṇavatthārakena desemi, ṭhapetvā thullavajjaṃ, ṭhapetvā gihippaṭisaṃyuttaṃ.**For the benefit of these venerables and myself, I confess in the midst of the Sangha both their and my own offenses by covering over as if with grass, except for heavy offenses and offenses connected with householders.*";
P_HTM[5404]="*Yassāyasmato khamati amhākaṃ imāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ saṅghamajjhe tiṇavatthārakena desanā, ṭhapetvā thullavajjaṃ, ṭhapetvā gihippaṭisaṃyuttaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of the confession in the midst of the Sangha of both their and my own offenses by covering over as if with grass, except for heavy offenses and offenses connected with householders should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[5405]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[5406]="*Desitā amhākaṃ imā āpattiyo saṅghamajjhe tiṇavatthārakena, ṭhapetvā thullavajjaṃ, ṭhapetvā gihippaṭisaṃyuttaṃ.**We have confessed these offenses in the midst of the Sangha by covering over as if with grass, except for heavy offenses and offenses connected with householders.*";
P_HTM[5407]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[5408]="*Athāparesaṃ ekatopakkhikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**“A competent and capable monk belonging to the other side should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[5409]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5410]="*Amhākaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ viharataṃ bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**While we were arguing and disputing, we did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5411]="*Sace mayaṃ imāhi āpattīhi aññamaññaṃ kāressāma, siyāpi taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ kakkhaḷattāya vāḷattāya bhedāya saṃvatteyya.**If we deal with one another for these offenses, this legal issue might lead to harshness, nastiness, and schism.*";
P_HTM[5412]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, ahaṃ yā ceva imesaṃ āyasmantānaṃ āpatti, yā ca attano āpatti, imesañceva āyasmantānaṃ atthāya, attano ca atthāya, saṅghamajjhe tiṇavatthārakena deseyyaṃ, ṭhapetvā thullavajjaṃ, ṭhapetvā gihippaṭisaṃyuttaṃ.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, then for the benefit of these venerables and myself, I will confess in the midst of the Sangha both their and my own offenses by covering over as if with grass, except for heavy offenses and offenses connected with householders.*";
P_HTM[5413]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[5414]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5415]="*Amhākaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ viharataṃ bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**While we were arguing and disputing, we did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5416]="*Sace mayaṃ imāhi āpattīhi aññamaññaṃ kāressāma, siyāpi taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ kakkhaḷattāya vāḷattāya bhedāya saṃvatteyya.**If we deal with one another for these offenses, this legal issue might lead to harshness, nastiness, and schism.*";
P_HTM[5417]="*Ahaṃ yā ceva imesaṃ āyasmantānaṃ āpatti, yā ca attano āpatti, imesañceva āyasmantānaṃ atthāya, attano ca atthāya, saṅghamajjhe tiṇavatthārakena desemi, ṭhapetvā thullavajjaṃ, ṭhapetvā gihippaṭisaṃyuttaṃ.**For the benefit of these venerables and myself, I confess in the midst of the Sangha both their and my own offenses by covering over as if with grass, except for heavy offenses and offenses connected with householders.*";
P_HTM[5418]="*Yassāyasmato khamati amhākaṃ imāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ saṅghamajjhe tiṇavatthārakena desanā, ṭhapetvā thullavajjaṃ, ṭhapetvā gihippaṭisaṃyuttaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of the confession in the midst of the Sangha of both their and my own offenses by covering over as if with grass, except for heavy offenses and offenses connected with householders should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[5419]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[5420]="*Desitā amhākaṃ imā āpattiyo saṅghamajjhe tiṇavatthārakena, ṭhapetvā thullavajjaṃ, ṭhapetvā gihippaṭisaṃyuttaṃ.**We have confessed these offenses in the midst of the Sangha by covering over as if with grass, except for heavy offenses and offenses connected with householders.*";
P_HTM[5421]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[5422]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, te bhikkhū tāhi āpattīhi vuṭṭhitā honti, ṭhapetvā thullavajjaṃ, ṭhapetvā gihippaṭisaṃyuttaṃ, ṭhapetvā diṭṭhāvikammaṃ, ṭhapetvā ye na tattha hontī”ti.**“In this way those monks are cleared of those offenses, except for heavy offenses and offenses connected with householders, and except for those monks who state their objection and those who are absent.”*";
P_HTM[5423]="*8. Adhikaraṇa**8. Legal issues*";
P_HTM[5424]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhūpi bhikkhūhi vivadanti, bhikkhūpi bhikkhunīhi vivadanti, bhikkhuniyopi bhikkhūhi vivadanti, channopi bhikkhu bhikkhunīnaṃ anupakhajja bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ vivadati, bhikkhunīnaṃ pakkhaṃ gāheti.**On one occasion monks were disputing with monks, monks with nuns, and nuns with monks. Standing with the nuns, the monk Channa disputed with the monks, making others side with the nuns.*";
P_HTM[5425]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[5426]="*“kathañhi nāma channo bhikkhu bhikkhunīnaṃ anupakhajja bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ vivadissati, bhikkhunīnaṃ pakkhaṃ gāhessatīti.**“How can the monk Channa act like this?”*";
P_HTM[5427]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha of monks gathered and questioned them:*";
P_HTM[5428]="*saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave …pe…**“Is it true, monks, that the monk Channa is acting like this?”*";
P_HTM[5429]="*saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5430]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing him …*";
P_HTM[5431]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[5432]="*“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇāni— vivādādhikaraṇaṃ, anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, kiccādhikaraṇaṃ.**“Monks, there are four kinds of legal issues: legal issues arising from disputes; legal issues arising from accusations; legal issues arising from offenses; legal issues arising from business.*";
P_HTM[5433]="*Tattha katamaṃ vivādādhikaraṇaṃ?**(1a) What is a legal issue arising from a dispute?*";
P_HTM[5434]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhū vivadanti—**It may be that the monks are disputing, saying,*";
P_HTM[5435]="*dhammoti vā adhammoti vā, vinayoti vā avinayoti vā, bhāsitaṃ lapitaṃ tathāgatenāti vā abhāsitaṃ alapitaṃ tathāgatenāti vā, āciṇṇaṃ tathāgatenāti vā anāciṇṇaṃ tathāgatenāti vā, paññattaṃ tathāgatenāti vā apaññattaṃ tathāgatenāti vā, āpattīti vā anāpattīti vā, lahukā āpattīti vā garukā āpattīti vā, sāvasesā āpattīti vā anavasesā āpattīti vā, duṭṭhullā āpattīti vā aduṭṭhullā āpattīti vā?**‘This is the Teaching’, ‘This is contrary to the Teaching’, ‘This is the Monastic Law’, ‘This is contrary to the Monastic Law’, ‘This was spoken by the Buddha’, ‘This was not spoken by the Buddha’, ‘This was practiced by the Buddha’, ‘This was not practiced by the Buddha’, ‘This was laid down by the Buddha’, ‘This was not laid down by the Buddha’, ‘This is an offense’, ‘This is not an offense’, ‘This is a light offense’, ‘This is a heavy offense’, ‘This is a curable offense’, ‘This is an incurable offense’, ‘This is a grave offense’, or ‘This is a minor offense.’*";
P_HTM[5436]="*Yaṃ tattha bhaṇḍanaṃ kalaho viggaho vivādo nānāvādo aññathāvādo vipaccatāya vohāro medhagaṃ—**In regard to this, whatever quarreling, arguing, conflict, disputing, variety in opinion, difference in opinion, heated speech, or strife there is—*";
P_HTM[5437]="*idaṃ vuccati vivādādhikaraṇaṃ.**this is called a legal issue arising from a dispute.*";
P_HTM[5438]="*Tattha katamaṃ anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ?**(1b) What is a legal issue arising from an accusation?*";
P_HTM[5439]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhū bhikkhuṃ anuvadanti sīlavipattiyā vā ācāravipattiyā vā diṭṭhivipattiyā vā ājīvavipattiyā vā.**It may be that the monks accuse a monk of failure in morality, failure in conduct, failure in view, or failure in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[5440]="*Yo tattha anuvādo anuvadanā anullapanā anubhaṇanā anusampavaṅkatā abbhussahanatā anubalappadānaṃ—**In regard to this, whatever accusation, accusing, allegation, blame, taking sides because of friendship, taking part in the accusation, or supporting the accusation there is—*";
P_HTM[5441]="*idaṃ vuccati anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ.**this is called a legal issue arising from an accusation.*";
P_HTM[5442]="*Tattha katamaṃ āpattādhikaraṇaṃ?**(1c) What is a legal issue arising from an offense?*";
P_HTM[5443]="*Pañcapi āpattikkhandhā āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, sattapi āpattikkhandhā āpattādhikaraṇaṃ—**There are legal issues arising from offenses because of the five classes of offenses; there are legal issues arising from offenses because of the seven classes of offenses—*";
P_HTM[5444]="*idaṃ vuccati āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**this is called a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[5445]="*Tattha katamaṃ kiccādhikaraṇaṃ?**(1d) What is a legal issue arising from business?*";
P_HTM[5446]="*Yā saṅghassa kiccayatā, karaṇīyatā, apalokanakammaṃ, ñattikammaṃ, ñattidutiyakammaṃ, ñatticatutthakammaṃ—**Whatever is the duty or the business of the Sangha—a legal procedure consisting of getting permission, a legal procedure consisting of one motion, a legal procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement, a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements—*";
P_HTM[5447]="*idaṃ vuccati kiccādhikaraṇaṃ.**this is called a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[5448]="*Vivādādhikaraṇassa kiṃ mūlaṃ?**(2a) What is the root of legal issues arising from disputes?*";
P_HTM[5449]="*Cha vivādamūlāni vivādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ.**There are six roots of disputes that in turn are the root of legal issues arising from disputes.*";
P_HTM[5450]="*Tīṇipi akusalamūlāni vivādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ, tīṇipi kusalamūlāni vivādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ.**There are also three unwholesome and three wholesome roots of legal issues arising from disputes.*";
P_HTM[5451]="*Katamāni cha vivādamūlāni vivādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ?**What are the six roots of disputes that in turn are the root of legal issues arising from disputes?*";
P_HTM[5452]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kodhano hoti upanāhī.**It may be that a monk is angry and resentful.*";
P_HTM[5453]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kodhano hoti upanāhī, so sattharipi agāravo viharati appatisso, dhammepi agāravo viharati appatisso, saṅghepi agāravo viharati appatisso, sikkhāyapi na paripūrakārī hoti.**One who is angry and resentful is disrespectful and undeferential toward the Teacher, the Teaching, and the Sangha, and he doesn’t fulfill the training.*";
P_HTM[5454]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sattharipi agāravo viharati appatisso, dhammepi …pe…**Such a person*";
P_HTM[5455]="*saṅghepi …pe…* **";
P_HTM[5456]="*sikkhāyapi na paripūrakārī, so saṅghe vivādaṃ janeti.**creates disputes in the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[5457]="*Yo hoti vivādo bahujanāhitāya bahujanāsukhāya bahuno janassa anatthāya ahitāya dukkhāya devamanussānaṃ.**Disputes are unbeneficial and a cause of unhappiness for humanity; they are harmful, detrimental, and a cause of suffering for gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[5458]="*Evarūpañce tumhe, bhikkhave, vivādamūlaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā samanupasseyyātha, tatra tumhe, bhikkhave, tasseva pāpakassa vivādamūlassa pahānāya vāyameyyātha.**Monks, when you see such a root of disputes either in yourself or in others, you should make an effort to get rid of it.*";
P_HTM[5459]="*Evarūpañce tumhe, bhikkhave, vivādamūlaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā na samanupasseyyātha, tatra tumhe, bhikkhave, tasseva pāpakassa vivādamūlassa āyatiṃ anavassavāya paṭipajjeyyātha.**If you don’t see such a root either in yourself or in others, you should practice so that it doesn’t reappear in the future.*";
P_HTM[5460]="*Evametassa pāpakassa vivādamūlassa pahānaṃ hoti.**In this way that bad root of disputes is abandoned.*";
P_HTM[5461]="*Evametassa pāpakassa vivādamūlassa āyatiṃ anavassavo hoti.* **";
P_HTM[5462]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu makkhī hoti paḷāsī …pe…**Or it may be that a monk is denigrating and controlling,*";
P_HTM[5463]="*issukī hoti maccharī, saṭho hoti māyāvī, pāpiccho hoti micchādiṭṭhī, sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī hoti ādhānaggāhī duppaṭinissaggī.**envious and stingy, treacherous and deceitful, one who has bad desires and wrong views, or one who obstinately grasps his own views and only gives them up with difficulty.*";
P_HTM[5464]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī hoti ādhānaggāhī duppaṭinissaggī, so sattharipi agāravo viharati appatisso, dhammepi agāravo viharati appatisso, saṅghepi agāravo viharati appatisso, sikkhāyapi na paripūrakārī hoti.**Any of these is disrespectful and undeferential toward the Teacher, the Teaching, and the Sangha, and he doesn’t fulfill the training.*";
P_HTM[5465]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sattharipi agāravo viharati appatisso, dhammepi …pe…**Such a person*";
P_HTM[5466]="*saṅghepi …pe…* **";
P_HTM[5467]="*sikkhāyapi na paripūrakārī, so saṅghe vivādaṃ janeti.**creates disputes in the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[5468]="*Yo hoti vivādo bahujanāhitāya bahujanāsukhāya bahuno janassa anatthāya ahitāya dukkhāya devamanussānaṃ.**Disputes are unbeneficial and a cause of unhappiness for humanity; they are harmful, detrimental, and a cause of suffering for gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[5469]="*Evarūpañce tumhe, bhikkhave, vivādamūlaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā samanupasseyyātha, tatra tumhe, bhikkhave, tasseva pāpakassa vivādamūlassa pahānāya vāyameyyātha.**Monks, when you see such a root of disputes either in yourself or in others, you should make an effort to get rid of it.*";
P_HTM[5470]="*Evarūpañce tumhe, bhikkhave, vivādamūlaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā na samanupasseyyātha, tatra tumhe, bhikkhave, tasseva pāpakassa vivādamūlassa āyatiṃ anavassavāya paṭipajjeyyātha.**If you don’t see such a root either in yourself or in others, you should practice so that it doesn’t reappear in the future.*";
P_HTM[5471]="*Evametassa pāpakassa vivādamūlassa pahānaṃ hoti.**In this way that bad root of disputes is abandoned.*";
P_HTM[5472]="*Evametassa pāpakassa vivādamūlassa āyatiṃ anavassavo hoti.**In this way that bad root of disputes has no future effect.*";
P_HTM[5473]="*Imāni cha vivādamūlāni vivādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5474]="*Katamāni tīṇi akusalamūlāni vivādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ?**What are the three unwholesome roots of legal issues arising from disputes?*";
P_HTM[5475]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhū luddhacittā vivadanti, duṭṭhacittā vivadanti, mūḷhacittā vivadanti—**It may be that monks dispute with a mind of greed, with a mind of ill will, with a mind of delusion, saying,*";
P_HTM[5476]="*dhammoti vā adhammoti vā, vinayoti vā avinayoti vā, bhāsitaṃ lapitaṃ tathāgatenāti vā abhāsitaṃ alapitaṃ tathāgatenāti vā, āciṇṇaṃ tathāgatenāti vā anāciṇṇaṃ tathāgatenāti vā, paññattaṃ tathāgatenāti vā apaññattaṃ tathāgatenāti vā, āpattīti vā anāpattīti vā, lahukā āpattīti vā garukā āpattīti vā, sāvasesā āpattīti vā anavasesā āpattīti vā, duṭṭhullā āpattīti vā aduṭṭhullā āpattīti vā.**‘This is the Teaching’, ‘This is contrary to the Teaching’, ‘This is the Monastic Law’, ‘This is contrary to the Monastic Law’, ‘This was spoken by the Buddha’, ‘This was not spoken by the Buddha’, ‘This was practiced by the Buddha’, ‘This was not practiced by the Buddha’, ‘This was laid down by the Buddha’, ‘This was not laid down by the Buddha’, ‘This is an offense’, ‘This is not an offense’, ‘This is a light offense’, ‘This is a heavy offense’, ‘This is a curable offense’, ‘This is an incurable offense’, ‘This is a grave offense’, or ‘This is a minor offense.’*";
P_HTM[5477]="*Imāni tīṇi akusalamūlāni vivādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5478]="*Katamāni tīṇi kusalamūlāni vivādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ?**What are the three wholesome roots of legal issues arising from disputes?*";
P_HTM[5479]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhū aluddhacittā vivadanti, aduṭṭhacittā vivadanti, amūḷhacittā vivadanti—**It may be that monks dispute with a mind free from greed, free from ill will, free from delusion, saying,*";
P_HTM[5480]="*dhammoti vā adhammoti vā …pe…**‘This is the Teaching’, ‘This is contrary to the Teaching’ …*";
P_HTM[5481]="*duṭṭhullā āpattīti vā aduṭṭhullā āpattīti vā.**‘This is a grave offense’, or ‘This is a minor offense.’*";
P_HTM[5482]="*Imāni tīṇi kusalamūlāni vivādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5483]="*“Anuvādādhikaraṇassa kiṃ mūlaṃ?**(2b) What is the root of legal issues arising from accusations?*";
P_HTM[5484]="*Cha anuvādamūlāni anuvādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ.**There are six roots of accusations that in turn are the root of legal issues arising from accusations.*";
P_HTM[5485]="*Tīṇipi akusalamūlāni anuvādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ, tīṇipi kusalamūlāni anuvādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ, kāyopi anuvādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ, vācāpi anuvādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ.**There are also three unwholesome and three wholesome roots of legal issues arising from accusations. The body, too, is a root of legal issues arising from accusations, and so is speech.*";
P_HTM[5486]="*Katamāni cha anuvādamūlāni anuvādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ?**What are the six roots of accusations that in turn are the root of legal issues arising from accusations?*";
P_HTM[5487]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kodhano hoti upanāhī.**It may be that a monk is angry and resentful.*";
P_HTM[5488]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kodhano hoti upanāhī, so sattharipi agāravo viharati appatisso, dhammepi agāravo viharati appatisso, saṅghepi agāravo viharati appatisso, sikkhāyapi na paripūrakārī hoti.**One who is angry and resentful is disrespectful and undeferential toward the Teacher, the Teaching, and the Sangha, and he doesn’t fulfill the training.*";
P_HTM[5489]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sattharipi agāravo viharati appatisso, dhammepi …pe…**Such a person*";
P_HTM[5490]="*saṅghepi …pe…* **";
P_HTM[5491]="*sikkhāyapi na paripūrakārī, so saṅghe anuvādaṃ janeti.**creates accusations in the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[5492]="*Yo hoti anuvādo bahujanāhitāya bahujanāsukhāya bahuno janassa anatthāya ahitāya dukkhāya devamanussānaṃ.**Accusations are unbeneficial and a cause of unhappiness for humanity; they are harmful, detrimental, and a cause of suffering for gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[5493]="*Evarūpañce tumhe, bhikkhave, anuvādamūlaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā samanupasseyyātha, tatra tumhe, bhikkhave, tasseva pāpakassa anuvādamūlassa pahānāya vāyameyyātha.**Monks, when you see such a root of accusations either in yourself or in others, you should make an effort to get rid of it.*";
P_HTM[5494]="*Evarūpañce tumhe, bhikkhave, anuvādamūlaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā na samanupasseyyātha, tatra tumhe, bhikkhave, tasseva pāpakassa anuvādamūlassa āyatiṃ anavassavāya paṭipajjeyyātha.**If you don’t see such a root either in yourself or in others, you should practice so that it doesn’t reappear in the future.*";
P_HTM[5495]="*Evametassa pāpakassa anuvādamūlassa pahānaṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[5496]="*Evametassa pāpakassa anuvādamūlassa āyatiṃ anavassavo hoti.* **";
P_HTM[5497]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu makkhī hoti paḷāsī …pe…**Or it may be that a monk is denigrating and controlling,*";
P_HTM[5498]="*issukī hoti maccharī, saṭho hoti māyāvī, pāpiccho hoti micchādiṭṭhī, sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī hoti ādhānaggāhī duppaṭinissaggī.**envious and stingy, treacherous and deceitful, one who has bad desires and wrong views, or one who obstinately grasps his own views and only gives them up with difficulty.*";
P_HTM[5499]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī hoti ādhānaggāhī duppaṭinissaggī, so sattharipi agāravo viharati appatisso, dhammepi agāravo viharati appatisso, saṅghepi agāravo viharati appatisso, sikkhāyapi na paripūrakārī hoti.**Any of these is disrespectful and undeferential toward the Teacher, the Teaching, and the Sangha, and he doesn’t fulfill the training.*";
P_HTM[5500]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sattharipi agāravo viharati appatisso, dhammepi …pe…**Such a person*";
P_HTM[5501]="*saṅghepi …pe…* **";
P_HTM[5502]="*sikkhāyapi na paripūrakārī, so saṅghe anuvādaṃ janeti.**creates accusations in the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[5503]="*Yo hoti anuvādo bahujanāhitāya bahujanāsukhāya bahuno janassa anatthāya ahitāya dukkhāya devamanussānaṃ.**Accusations are unbeneficial and a cause of unhappiness for humanity; they are harmful, detrimental, and a cause of suffering for gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[5504]="*Evarūpañce tumhe, bhikkhave, anuvādamūlaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā samanupasseyyātha, tatra tumhe, bhikkhave, tasseva pāpakassa anuvādamūlassa pahānāya vāyameyyātha.**Monks, when you see such a root of accusations either in yourself or in others, you should make an effort to get rid of it.*";
P_HTM[5505]="*Evarūpañce tumhe, bhikkhave, anuvādamūlaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā na samanupasseyyātha, tatra tumhe, bhikkhave, tasseva pāpakassa anuvādamūlassa āyatiṃ anavassavāya paṭipajjeyyātha.**If you don’t see such a root either in yourself or in others, you should practice so that it doesn’t reappear in the future.*";
P_HTM[5506]="*Evametassa pāpakassa anuvādamūlassa pahānaṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[5507]="*Evametassa pāpakassa anuvādamūlassa āyatiṃ anavassavo hoti.* **";
P_HTM[5508]="*Imāni cha anuvādamūlāni anuvādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5509]="*Katamāni tīṇi akusalamūlāni anuvādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ?**What are the three unwholesome roots of accusations?*";
P_HTM[5510]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhū bhikkhuṃ luddhacittā anuvadanti, duṭṭhacittā anuvadanti, mūḷhacittā anuvadanti—**It may be that monks, because of greed, because of ill will, because of delusion, accuse others of*";
P_HTM[5511]="*sīlavipattiyā vā, ācāravipattiyā vā, diṭṭhivipattiyā vā, ājīvavipattiyā vā.**failure in morality, failure in conduct, failure in view, or failure in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[5512]="*Imāni tīṇi akusalamūlāni anuvādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5513]="*Katamāni tīṇi kusalamūlāni anuvādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ?**What are the three wholesome roots of accusations?*";
P_HTM[5514]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhū bhikkhuṃ aluddhacittā anuvadanti, aduṭṭhacittā anuvadanti, amūḷhacittā anuvadanti—**It may be that monks, because of non-greed, because of non-ill will, because of non-delusion, accuse others of*";
P_HTM[5515]="*sīlavipattiyā vā, ācāravipattiyā vā, diṭṭhivipattiyā vā, ājīvavipattiyā vā.**failure in morality, failure in conduct, failure in view, or failure in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[5516]="*Imāni tīṇi kusalamūlāni anuvādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5517]="*Katamo kāyo anuvādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ?**How is the body a root of legal issues arising from accusations?*";
P_HTM[5518]="*Idhekacco dubbaṇṇo hoti, duddassiko, okoṭimako, bahvābādho, kāṇo vā, kuṇī vā, khañjo vā, pakkhahato vā, yena naṃ anuvadanti.**It may be that someone is ugly, unsightly, a dwarf, sickly, blind in one eye, crooked-limbed, lame, or paralyzed, and they blame him for that.*";
P_HTM[5519]="*Ayaṃ kāyo anuvādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5520]="*Katamā vācā anuvādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ?**How is speech a root of legal issues arising from accusations?*";
P_HTM[5521]="*Idhekacco dubbaco hoti, mammano, eḷagalavāco, yāya naṃ anuvadanti.**It may be that someone is difficult to correct, or he stutters or dribbles while speaking, and they blame him for that.*";
P_HTM[5522]="*Ayaṃ vācā anuvādādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5523]="*Āpattādhikaraṇassa kiṃ mūlaṃ?**(2c) What is the root of legal issues arising from offenses?*";
P_HTM[5524]="*Cha āpattisamuṭṭhānā āpattādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ.**There are six origins of offenses that in turn are the root of legal issues arising from offenses.*";
P_HTM[5525]="*Atthāpatti kāyato samuṭṭhāti, na vācato, na cittato.**There are offenses that originate from the body, but not from speech or the mind.*";
P_HTM[5526]="*Atthāpatti vācato samuṭṭhāti, na kāyato, na cittato.**There are offenses that originate from speech, but not from the body or the mind.*";
P_HTM[5527]="*Atthāpatti kāyato ca vācato ca samuṭṭhāti, na cittato.**There are offenses that originate from the body and speech, but not from the mind.*";
P_HTM[5528]="*Atthāpatti kāyato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti, na vācato.**There are offenses that originate from the body and the mind, but not from speech.*";
P_HTM[5529]="*Atthāpatti vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti, na kāyato.**There are offenses that originate from speech and the mind, but not from the body.*";
P_HTM[5530]="*Atthāpatti kāyato ca vācato ca cittato ca samuṭṭhāti.**There are offenses that originate from the body, speech, and the mind.*";
P_HTM[5531]="*Ime cha āpattisamuṭṭhānā āpattādhikaraṇassa mūlaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5532]="*Kiccādhikaraṇassa kiṃ mūlaṃ?**(2d) What is the root of legal issues arising from business?*";
P_HTM[5533]="*Kiccādhikaraṇassa ekaṃ mūlaṃ—**There is one root of legal issues arising from business:*";
P_HTM[5534]="*saṅgho.**the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[5535]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ kusalaṃ, akusalaṃ, abyākataṃ.**(3a) Is a legal issue arising from a dispute wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate?*";
P_HTM[5536]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ siyā kusalaṃ, siyā akusalaṃ, siyā abyākataṃ.**A legal issue arising from a dispute may be wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate.*";
P_HTM[5537]="*Tattha katamaṃ vivādādhikaraṇaṃ kusalaṃ?**What is a wholesome legal issue arising from a dispute?*";
P_HTM[5538]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhū kusalacittā vivadanti—**It may be that monks dispute with a wholesome mind, saying,*";
P_HTM[5539]="*dhammoti vā adhammoti vā …pe…**‘This is the Teaching’, ‘This is contrary to the Teaching’ …*";
P_HTM[5540]="*duṭṭhullā āpattīti vā aduṭṭhullā āpattīti vā.**‘This is a grave offense’, or ‘This is a minor offense.’*";
P_HTM[5541]="*Yaṃ tattha bhaṇḍanaṃ kalaho viggaho vivādo nānāvādo aññathāvādo vipaccatāya vohāro medhagaṃ—**In regard to this, whatever quarreling, arguing, conflict, disputing, variety in opinion, difference in opinion, heated speech, or strife there is—*";
P_HTM[5542]="*idaṃ vuccati vivādādhikaraṇaṃ kusalaṃ.**this is called a wholesome legal issue arising from a dispute.*";
P_HTM[5543]="*Tattha katamaṃ vivādādhikaraṇaṃ akusalaṃ?**What is an unwholesome legal issue arising from a dispute?*";
P_HTM[5544]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhū akusalacittā vivadanti—**It may be that monks dispute with an unwholesome mind, saying,*";
P_HTM[5545]="*dhammoti vā adhammoti vā …pe…**‘This is the Teaching’, or ‘This is contrary to the Teaching’ …*";
P_HTM[5546]="*duṭṭhullā āpattīti vā aduṭṭhullā āpattīti vā.**‘This is a grave offense’, or ‘This is a minor offense.’*";
P_HTM[5547]="*Yaṃ tattha bhaṇḍanaṃ kalaho viggaho vivādo nānāvādo aññathāvādo vipaccatāya vohāro medhagaṃ—**In regard to this, whatever quarreling, arguing, conflict, disputing, variety in opinion, difference in opinion, heated speech, or strife there is—*";
P_HTM[5548]="*idaṃ vuccati vivādādhikaraṇaṃ akusalaṃ.**this is called an unwholesome legal issue arising from a dispute.*";
P_HTM[5549]="*Tattha katamaṃ vivādādhikaraṇaṃ abyākataṃ?**What is an indeterminate legal issue arising from a dispute?*";
P_HTM[5550]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhū abyākatacittā vivadanti—**It may be that monks dispute with an indeterminate mind, saying,*";
P_HTM[5551]="*dhammoti vā adhammoti vā …pe…**‘This is the Teaching’, or ‘This is contrary to the Teaching’ …*";
P_HTM[5552]="*duṭṭhullā āpattīti vā aduṭṭhullā āpattīti vā.**‘This is a grave offense’, or ‘This is a minor offense.’*";
P_HTM[5553]="*Yaṃ tattha bhaṇḍanaṃ kalaho viggaho vivādo nānāvādo aññathāvādo vipaccatāya vohāro medhagaṃ—**In regard to this, whatever quarreling, arguing, conflict, disputing, variety in opinion, difference in opinion, heated speech, or strife there is—*";
P_HTM[5554]="*idaṃ vuccati vivādādhikaraṇaṃ abyākataṃ.**this is called an indeterminate legal issue arising from a dispute.*";
P_HTM[5555]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ kusalaṃ, akusalaṃ, abyākataṃ.**(3b) Is a legal issue arising from an accusation wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate?*";
P_HTM[5556]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ siyā kusalaṃ, siyā akusalaṃ, siyā abyākataṃ.**A legal issue arising from an accusation may be wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate.*";
P_HTM[5557]="*Tattha katamaṃ anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ kusalaṃ?**What is a wholesome legal issue arising from an accusation?*";
P_HTM[5558]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhū bhikkhuṃ kusalacittā anuvadanti—**It may be that monks with wholesome minds accuse a monk*";
P_HTM[5559]="*sīlavipattiyā vā, ācāravipattiyā vā, diṭṭhivipattiyā vā, ājīvavipattiyā vā.**of failure in morality, failure in conduct, failure in view, or failure in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[5560]="*Yo tattha anuvādo anuvadanā anullapanā anubhaṇanā anusampavaṅkatā abbhussahanatā anubalappadānaṃ—**In regard to this, whatever accusation, accusing, allegation, blame, taking sides because of friendship, taking part in the accusation, or supporting the accusation there is—*";
P_HTM[5561]="*idaṃ vuccati anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ kusalaṃ.**this is called a wholesome legal issue arising from an accusation.*";
P_HTM[5562]="*Tattha katamaṃ anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ akusalaṃ?**What is an unwholesome legal issue arising from an accusation?*";
P_HTM[5563]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhū bhikkhuṃ akusalacittā anuvadanti—**It may be that monks with unwholesome minds accuse a monk*";
P_HTM[5564]="*sīlavipattiyā vā, ācāravipattiyā vā, diṭṭhivipattiyā vā, ājīvavipattiyā vā.**of failure in morality, failure in conduct, failure in view, or failure in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[5565]="*Yo tattha anuvādo anuvadanā anullapanā anubhaṇanā anusampavaṅkatā abbhussahanatā anubalappadānaṃ—**In regard to this, whatever accusation, accusing, allegation, blame, taking sides because of friendship, taking part in the accusation, or supporting the accusation there is—*";
P_HTM[5566]="*idaṃ vuccati anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ akusalaṃ.**this is called an unwholesome legal issue arising from an accusation.*";
P_HTM[5567]="*Tattha katamaṃ anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ abyākataṃ?**What is an indeterminate legal issue arising from an accusation?*";
P_HTM[5568]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhū bhikkhuṃ abyākatacittā anuvadanti—**It may be that monks with indeterminate minds accuse a monk*";
P_HTM[5569]="*sīlavipattiyā vā, ācāravipattiyā vā, diṭṭhivipattiyā vā, ājīvavipattiyā vā.**of failure in morality, failure in conduct, failure in view, or failure in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[5570]="*Yo tattha anuvādo anuvadanā anullapanā anubhaṇanā anusampavaṅkatā abbhussahanatā anubalappadānaṃ—**In regard to this, whatever accusation, accusing, allegation, blame, taking sides because of friendship, taking part in the accusation, or supporting the accusation there is—*";
P_HTM[5571]="*idaṃ vuccati anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ abyākataṃ.**this is called an indeterminate legal issue arising from an accusation.*";
P_HTM[5572]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ kusalaṃ, akusalaṃ, abyākataṃ?**(3c) Is a legal issue arising from an offense wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate?*";
P_HTM[5573]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ siyā akusalaṃ, siyā abyākataṃ;**A legal issue arising from an offense may be unwholesome or indeterminate.*";
P_HTM[5574]="*natthi āpattādhikaraṇaṃ kusalaṃ.**There are no wholesome legal issues arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[5575]="*Tattha katamaṃ āpattādhikaraṇaṃ akusalaṃ?**What is an unwholesome legal issue arising from an offense?*";
P_HTM[5576]="*Yaṃ jānanto sañjānanto cecca abhivitaritvā vītikkamo—**When one transgresses, knowing, perceiving, having intended, having decided—*";
P_HTM[5577]="*idaṃ vuccati āpattādhikaraṇaṃ akusalaṃ.**this is called an unwholesome legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[5578]="*Tattha katamaṃ āpattādhikaraṇaṃ abyākataṃ?**What is an indeterminate legal issue arising from an offense?*";
P_HTM[5579]="*Yaṃ ajānanto asañjānanto acecca anabhivitaritvā vītikkamo—**When one transgresses, not knowing, not perceiving, not having intended, not having decided—*";
P_HTM[5580]="*idaṃ vuccati āpattādhikaraṇaṃ abyākataṃ.**this is called an indeterminate legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[5581]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ kusalaṃ, akusalaṃ, abyākataṃ?**(3d) Is a legal issue arising from business wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate?*";
P_HTM[5582]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ siyā kusalaṃ, siyā akusalaṃ, siyā abyākataṃ.**A legal issue arising from business may be wholesome, unwholesome, or indeterminate.*";
P_HTM[5583]="*Tattha katamaṃ kiccādhikaraṇaṃ kusalaṃ?**What is a wholesome legal issue arising from business?*";
P_HTM[5584]="*Yaṃ saṅgho kusalacitto kammaṃ karoti—**When the Sangha does a legal procedure with a wholesome mind—*";
P_HTM[5585]="*apalokanakammaṃ, ñattikammaṃ, ñattidutiyakammaṃ, ñatticatutthakammaṃ—**whether a procedure consisting of getting permission, a procedure consisting of one motion, a procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement, or a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements—*";
P_HTM[5586]="*idaṃ vuccati kiccādhikaraṇaṃ kusalaṃ.**this is called a wholesome legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[5587]="*Tattha katamaṃ kiccādhikaraṇaṃ akusalaṃ?**What is an unwholesome legal issue arising from business?*";
P_HTM[5588]="*Yaṃ saṅgho akusalacitto kammaṃ karoti—**When the Sangha does a legal procedure with an unwholesome mind—*";
P_HTM[5589]="*apalokanakammaṃ, ñattikammaṃ, ñattidutiyakammaṃ, ñatticatutthakammaṃ—**whether a procedure consisting of getting permission, a procedure consisting of one motion, a procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement, or a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements—*";
P_HTM[5590]="*idaṃ vuccati kiccādhikaraṇaṃ akusalaṃ.**this is called an unwholesome legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[5591]="*Tattha katamaṃ kiccādhikaraṇaṃ abyākataṃ?**What is an indeterminate legal issue arising from business?*";
P_HTM[5592]="*Yaṃ saṅgho abyākatacitto kammaṃ karoti—**When the Sangha does a legal procedure with an indeterminate mind—*";
P_HTM[5593]="*apalokanakammaṃ, ñattikammaṃ, ñattidutiyakammaṃ, ñatticatutthakammaṃ—**whether a procedure consisting of getting permission, a procedure consisting of one motion, a procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement, or a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements—*";
P_HTM[5594]="*idaṃ vuccati kiccādhikaraṇaṃ abyākataṃ.**this is called an indeterminate legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[5595]="*Vivādo vivādādhikaraṇaṃ, vivādo no adhikaraṇaṃ, adhikaraṇaṃ no vivādo, adhikaraṇañceva vivādo ca.**(4a) Are there disputes that are a legal issue arising from a dispute? Are there disputes that are not a legal issue? Are there legal issues that are not a dispute? Are there legal issues that are also a dispute?*";
P_HTM[5596]="*Siyā vivādo vivādādhikaraṇaṃ, siyā vivādo no adhikaraṇaṃ, siyā adhikaraṇaṃ no vivādo, siyā adhikaraṇañceva vivādo ca.**There may be disputes that are a legal issue arising from a dispute; there may be disputes that are not a legal issue; there may be legal issues that are not a dispute; there may be legal issues that are also a dispute.*";
P_HTM[5597]="*Tattha katamo vivādo vivādādhikaraṇaṃ?**How is there a dispute that is a legal issue arising from a dispute?*";
P_HTM[5598]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhū vivadanti—**It may be that monks are disputing, saying,*";
P_HTM[5599]="*dhammoti vā adhammoti vā …pe…**‘This is the Teaching’, or ‘This is contrary to the Teaching’ …*";
P_HTM[5600]="*duṭṭhullā āpattīti vā aduṭṭhullā āpattīti vā.**‘This is a grave offense’, or ‘This is a minor offense.’*";
P_HTM[5601]="*Yaṃ tattha bhaṇḍanaṃ kalaho viggaho vivādo nānāvādo aññathāvādo vipaccatāya vohāro medhagaṃ—**In regard to this, whatever there is of quarreling, arguing, conflict, disputing, variety in opinion, difference in opinion, heated speech, or strife—*";
P_HTM[5602]="*ayaṃ vivādo vivādādhikaraṇaṃ.**this is a dispute that is a legal issue arising from a dispute.*";
P_HTM[5603]="*Tattha katamo vivādo no adhikaraṇaṃ?**How is there a dispute that is not a legal issue?*";
P_HTM[5604]="*Mātāpi puttena vivadati, puttopi mātarā vivadati, pitāpi puttena vivadati, puttopi pitarā vivadati, bhātāpi bhātarā vivadati, bhātāpi bhaginiyā vivadati, bhaginīpi bhātarā vivadati, sahāyopi sahāyena vivadati—**A mother disputes with her child; a child with their mother; a father with his child; a child with their father; a brother with his brother; a brother with his sister; a sister with her brother; a friend with their friend—*";
P_HTM[5605]="*ayaṃ vivādo no adhikaraṇaṃ.**this is a dispute that is not a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[5606]="*Tattha katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ no vivādo?**How is there a legal issue that is not a dispute?*";
P_HTM[5607]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, kiccādhikaraṇaṃ—**A legal issue arising from an accusation, a legal issue arising from an offense, a legal issue arising from business—*";
P_HTM[5608]="*idaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ no vivādo.**this is a legal issue that is not a dispute.*";
P_HTM[5609]="*Tattha katamaṃ adhikaraṇañceva vivādo ca?**How is there a legal issue that is also a dispute?*";
P_HTM[5610]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ adhikaraṇañceva vivādo ca.**A legal issue arising from a dispute is a legal issue and also a dispute.*";
P_HTM[5611]="*Anuvādo anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ, anuvādo no adhikaraṇaṃ, adhikaraṇaṃ no anuvādo, adhikaraṇañceva anuvādo ca.**(4b) Are there accusations that are a legal issue arising from an accusation? Are there accusations that are not a legal issue? Are there legal issues that are not an accusation? Are there legal issues that are also an accusation?*";
P_HTM[5612]="*Siyā anuvādo anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ, siyā anuvādo no adhikaraṇaṃ, siyā adhikaraṇaṃ no anuvādo, siyā adhikaraṇañceva anuvādo ca.**There may be accusations that are a legal issue arising from an accusation; there may be accusations that are not a legal issue; there may be legal issues that are not an accusation; there may legal issues that are also an accusation.*";
P_HTM[5613]="*Tattha katamo anuvādo anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ?**How is there an accusation that is a legal issue arising from an accusation?*";
P_HTM[5614]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhū bhikkhuṃ anuvadanti—**It may be that monks accuse a monk*";
P_HTM[5615]="*sīlavipattiyā vā, ācāravipattiyā vā, diṭṭhivipattiyā vā, ājīvavipattiyā vā.**of failure in morality, failure in conduct, failure in view, or failure in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[5616]="*Yo tattha anuvādo anuvadanā anullapanā anubhaṇanā anusampavaṅkatā abbhussahanatā anubalappadānaṃ—**In regard to this, whatever there is of accusation, accusing, allegation, blame, taking sides because of friendship, taking part in the accusation, or supporting the accusation—*";
P_HTM[5617]="*ayaṃ anuvādo anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ.**this is an accusation that is a legal issue arising from an accusation.*";
P_HTM[5618]="*Tattha katamo anuvādo no adhikaraṇaṃ?**How is there an accusation that is not a legal issue?*";
P_HTM[5619]="*Mātāpi puttaṃ anuvadati, puttopi mātaraṃ anuvadati, pitāpi puttaṃ anuvadati, puttopi pitaraṃ anuvadati, bhātāpi bhātaraṃ anuvadati, bhātāpi bhaginiṃ anuvadati, bhaginīpi bhātaraṃ anuvadati, sahāyopi sahāyaṃ anuvadati—**A mother accuses her child; a child their mother; a father his child; a child their father; a brother his brother; a brother his sister; a sister her brother; a friend their friend—*";
P_HTM[5620]="*ayaṃ anuvādo no adhikaraṇaṃ.**this is an accusation that is not a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[5621]="*Tattha katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ no anuvādo?**How is there a legal issue that is not an accusation?*";
P_HTM[5622]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, kiccādhikaraṇaṃ, vivādādhikaraṇaṃ—**A legal issue arising from an offense, a legal issue arising from business, a legal issue arising from a dispute—*";
P_HTM[5623]="*idaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ no anuvādo.**this is a legal issue that is not an accusation.*";
P_HTM[5624]="*Tattha katamaṃ adhikaraṇañceva anuvādo ca?**How is there a legal issue that is also an accusation?*";
P_HTM[5625]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ adhikaraṇañceva anuvādo ca.**A legal issue arising from an accusation is a legal issue and also an accusation.*";
P_HTM[5626]="*Āpatti āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, āpatti no adhikaraṇaṃ, adhikaraṇaṃ no āpatti, adhikaraṇañceva āpatti ca.**(4c) Are there  offenses that are a legal issue arising from an offense? Are there offenses that are not a legal issue? Are there legal issues that are not an offense? Are there legal issues that are also an offense?*";
P_HTM[5627]="*Siyā āpatti āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, siyā āpatti no adhikaraṇaṃ, siyā adhikaraṇaṃ no āpatti, siyā adhikaraṇañceva āpatti ca.**There may be offenses that are a legal issue arising from an offense; there may be offenses that are not a legal issue; there may be legal issues that are not an offense; there may be legal issues that are also an offense.*";
P_HTM[5628]="*Tattha katamaṃ āpatti āpattādhikaraṇaṃ?**How is there an offense that is a legal issue arising from an offense?*";
P_HTM[5629]="*Pañcapi āpattikkhandhā āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, sattapi āpattikkhandhā āpattādhikaraṇaṃ—**There is a legal issue arising from an offense because of the five classes of offenses; there is a legal issue arising from an offense because of the seven classes of offenses—*";
P_HTM[5630]="*ayaṃ āpatti āpattādhikaraṇaṃ.**this is an offense that is a legal issue arising from an offense.*";
P_HTM[5631]="*Tattha katamaṃ āpatti no adhikaraṇaṃ?**How is there an offense that is not a legal issue?*";
P_HTM[5632]="*Sotāpatti samāpatti—**The attainment of stream-entry—*";
P_HTM[5633]="*ayaṃ āpatti no adhikaraṇaṃ.**this is an attainment/offense that is not a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[5634]="*Tattha katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ no āpatti?**How is there a legal issue that is not an offense?*";
P_HTM[5635]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ, vivādādhikaraṇaṃ, anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ—**A legal issue arising from business, a legal issue arising from a dispute, a legal issue arising from an accusation—*";
P_HTM[5636]="*idaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ no āpatti.**this is a legal issue that is not an offense.*";
P_HTM[5637]="*Tattha katamaṃ adhikaraṇañceva āpatti ca?**How is there a legal issue that is also an offense?*";
P_HTM[5638]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ adhikaraṇañceva āpatti ca.**A legal issue arising from an offense is a legal issue and also an offense.*";
P_HTM[5639]="*Kiccaṃ kiccādhikaraṇaṃ, kiccaṃ no adhikaraṇaṃ, adhikaraṇaṃ no kiccaṃ, adhikaraṇañceva kiccañca.**(4d) Is there business that is a legal issue arising from business? Is there business that is not a legal issue? Are there legal issues that are not business? Are there legal issues that are also business?*";
P_HTM[5640]="*Siyā kiccaṃ kiccādhikaraṇaṃ, siyā kiccaṃ no adhikaraṇaṃ, siyā adhikaraṇaṃ no kiccaṃ, siyā adhikaraṇañceva kiccañca.**There may be business that is a legal issue arising from business; there may be business that is  not a legal issue; there may be legal issues that are not business; there may be legal issues that are also business.*";
P_HTM[5641]="*Tattha katamaṃ kiccaṃ kiccādhikaraṇaṃ?**How is there business that is a legal issue arising from business?*";
P_HTM[5642]="*Yā saṅghassa kiccayatā, karaṇīyatā, apalokanakammaṃ, ñattikammaṃ, ñattidutiyakammaṃ, ñatticatutthakammaṃ—**Whatever is the duty or the business of the Sangha—a legal procedure consisting of getting permission, a legal procedure consisting of one motion, a legal procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement, a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements—*";
P_HTM[5643]="*idaṃ kiccaṃ kiccādhikaraṇaṃ.**this is business that is a legal issue arising from business.*";
P_HTM[5644]="*Tattha katamaṃ kiccaṃ no adhikaraṇaṃ?**How is there business that is not a legal issue?*";
P_HTM[5645]="*Ācariyakiccaṃ, upajjhāyakiccaṃ, samānupajjhāyakiccaṃ, samānācariyakiccaṃ—**The duty to teacher, the duty to a preceptor, the duty to a co-student, the duty to a co-pupil—*";
P_HTM[5646]="*idaṃ kiccaṃ no adhikaraṇaṃ.**this is business that is not a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[5647]="*Tattha katamaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ no kiccaṃ?**How is there a legal issue that is not business?*";
P_HTM[5648]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ, anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ—**A legal issue arising from a dispute, a legal issue arising from an accusation, a legal issue arising from an offense—*";
P_HTM[5649]="*idaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ no kiccaṃ.**this is a legal issue that is not business.*";
P_HTM[5650]="*Tattha katamaṃ adhikaraṇañceva kiccañca?**How is there a legal issue that is also business?*";
P_HTM[5651]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ adhikaraṇañceva kiccañca.**A legal issue arising from business is a legal issue and also business.*";
P_HTM[5652]="*9. Adhikaraṇavūpasamanasamatha**9. The resolution and settling of legal issues*";
P_HTM[5653]="*9.1. Sammukhāvinaya**9.1 Resolution face-to-face*";
P_HTM[5654]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ katihi samathehi sammati?* **";
P_HTM[5655]="*Vivādādhikaraṇaṃ dvīhi samathehi sammati—**“There are two principles for settling a legal issue arising from a dispute:*";
P_HTM[5656]="*sammukhāvinayena ca, yebhuyyasikāya ca.**resolution face-to-face and majority decision.*";
P_HTM[5657]="*Siyā vivādādhikaraṇaṃ ekaṃ samathaṃ anāgamma yebhuyyasikaṃ, ekena samathena sameyya—**Can it be that a legal issue arising from a dispute should be settled not by majority decision,*";
P_HTM[5658]="*sammukhāvinayenāti?**but by resolution face-to-face?*";
P_HTM[5659]="*Siyātissa vacanīyaṃ.**It can.*";
P_HTM[5660]="*Yathā kathaṃ viya?**How is that?*";
P_HTM[5661]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhū vivadanti—**It may be that monks are disputing, saying,*";
P_HTM[5662]="*dhammoti vā adhammoti vā, vinayoti vā avinayoti vā, bhāsitaṃ lapitaṃ tathāgatenāti vā abhāsitaṃ alapitaṃ tathāgatenāti vā, āciṇṇaṃ tathāgatenāti vā anāciṇṇaṃ tathāgatenāti vā, paññattaṃ tathāgatenāti vā apaññattaṃ tathāgatenāti vā, āpattīti vā anāpattīti vā, lahukā āpattīti vā garukā āpattīti vā, sāvasesā āpattīti vā anavasesā āpattīti vā, duṭṭhullā āpattīti vā aduṭṭhullā āpattīti vā.**‘This is the Teaching’, ‘This is contrary to the Teaching’, ‘This is the Monastic Law’, ‘This is contrary to the Monastic Law’, ‘This was spoken by the Buddha’, ‘This was not spoken by the Buddha’, ‘This was practiced by the Buddha’, ‘This was not practiced by the Buddha’, ‘This was laid down by the Buddha’, ‘This was not laid down by the Buddha’, ‘This is an offense’, ‘This is not an offense’, ‘This is a light offense’, ‘This is a heavy offense’, ‘This is a curable offense’, ‘This is an incurable offense’, ‘This is a grave offense’, or ‘This is a minor offense.’*";
P_HTM[5663]="*Te ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhū sakkonti taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ, idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasantaṃ.**If those monks are able to resolve that legal issue, this is called the resolution of a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[5664]="*Kena vūpasantaṃ?* **";
P_HTM[5665]="*Sammukhāvinayena.**It has been resolved face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[5666]="*Kiñca tattha sammukhāvinayasmiṃ?**Face-to-face with what?*";
P_HTM[5667]="*Saṅghasammukhatā, dhammasammukhatā, vinayasammukhatā, puggalasammukhatā.**Face-to-face with the Sangha, face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law, face-to-face with the persons concerned.*";
P_HTM[5668]="*Kā ca tattha saṅghasammukhatā?**This is the meaning of face-to-face with the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[5669]="*Yāvatikā bhikkhū kammappattā te āgatā honti, chandārahānaṃ chando āhaṭo hoti, sammukhībhūtā na paṭikkosanti—**the monks who should be present have arrived, consent has been brought for those who are eligible to give their consent, and no one present objects to the decision.*";
P_HTM[5670]="*ayaṃ tattha saṅghasammukhatā.* **";
P_HTM[5671]="*Kā ca tattha dhammasammukhatā, vinayasammukhatā?**This is the meaning of face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law:*";
P_HTM[5672]="*Yena dhammena yena vinayena yena satthusāsanena taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati—**the Teaching, the Monastic Law, the Teacher’s instruction—that by which that legal issue is resolved.*";
P_HTM[5673]="*ayaṃ tattha dhammasammukhatā, vinayasammukhatā.* **";
P_HTM[5674]="*Kā ca tattha puggalasammukhatā?**This is the meaning of face-to-face with the persons concerned:*";
P_HTM[5675]="*Yo ca vivadati, yena ca vivadati, ubho atthapaccatthikā sammukhībhūtā honti—**both sides—those who are disputing and those they are disputing with—are present.*";
P_HTM[5676]="*ayaṃ tattha puggalasammukhatā.* **";
P_HTM[5677]="*Evaṃ vūpasantañce, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ kārako ukkoṭeti, ukkoṭanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ;**When a legal issue has been resolved like this, if any of the participants reopen it, they incur an offense entailing confession for the reopening.*";
P_HTM[5678]="*chandadāyako khīyati, khīyanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If anyone who gave their consent criticizes the resolution, they incur an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5679]="*Te ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhū na sakkonti taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ tasmiṃ āvāse vūpasametuṃ, tehi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūhi, yasmiṃ āvāse sambahulā bhikkhū, so āvāso gantabbo.**If those monks are unable to resolve that legal issue in that monastery, they should go to another monastery that has a number of monks.*";
P_HTM[5680]="*Te ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhū taṃ āvāsaṃ gacchantā antarāmagge sakkonti taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ, idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasantaṃ.**If they are able to resolve that legal issue while on their way, this is called the resolution of a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[5681]="*Kena vūpasantaṃ?* **";
P_HTM[5682]="*Sammukhāvinayena.**It has been resolved face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[5683]="*Kiñca tattha sammukhāvinayasmiṃ?**Face-to-face with what?*";
P_HTM[5684]="*Saṅghasammukhatā, dhammasammukhatā, vinayasammukhatā, puggalasammukhatā.**Face-to-face with the Sangha, face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law, face-to-face with the persons concerned.*";
P_HTM[5685]="*Kā ca tattha saṅghasammukhatā?**…*";
P_HTM[5686]="*Yāvatikā bhikkhū kammappattā te āgatā honti, chandārahānaṃ chando āhaṭo hoti, sammukhībhūtā na paṭikkosanti—* **";
P_HTM[5687]="*ayaṃ tattha saṅghasammukhatā.* **";
P_HTM[5688]="*Kā ca tattha dhammasammukhatā, vinayasammukhatā?* **";
P_HTM[5689]="*Yena dhammena yena vinayena yena satthusāsanena taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati—* **";
P_HTM[5690]="*ayaṃ tattha dhammasammukhatā, vinayasammukhatā.* **";
P_HTM[5691]="*Kā ca tattha puggalasammukhatā?* **";
P_HTM[5692]="*Yo ca vivadati, yena ca vivadati, ubho atthapaccatthikā sammukhībhūtā honti—* **";
P_HTM[5693]="*ayaṃ tattha puggalasammukhatā.* **";
P_HTM[5694]="*Evaṃ vūpasantañce, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ kārako ukkoṭeti, ukkoṭanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ;**When a legal issue has been resolved like this, if any of the participants reopen it, they incur an offense entailing confession for the reopening.*";
P_HTM[5695]="*chandadāyako khīyati, khīyanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If anyone who gave their consent criticizes the resolution, they incur an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5696]="*Te ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhū taṃ āvāsaṃ āgacchantā antarāmagge na sakkonti taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ, tehi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūhi, taṃ āvāsaṃ gantvā āvāsikā bhikkhū evamassu vacanīyā—**If those monks are unable to resolve that legal issue while on their way, they should go to that other monastery and say to the resident monks,*";
P_HTM[5697]="*‘idaṃ kho, āvuso, adhikaraṇaṃ evaṃ jātaṃ, evaṃ samuppannaṃ;**‘A legal issue has arisen in such-and-such a way.*";
P_HTM[5698]="*sādhāyasmantā imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasamentu dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena, yathayidaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ suvūpasantaṃ assā’ti.**It would be good if you would resolve it according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction, so that this legal issue may be properly resolved.’*";
P_HTM[5699]="*Sace, bhikkhave, āvāsikā bhikkhū vuḍḍhatarā honti, āgantukā bhikkhū navakatarā, tehi, bhikkhave, āvāsikehi bhikkhūhi āgantukā bhikkhū evamassu vacanīyā—**If the resident monks are senior to the visiting monks, the resident monks should say,*";
P_HTM[5700]="*‘iṅgha tumhe, āyasmanto, muhuttaṃ ekamantaṃ hotha, yāva mayaṃ mantemā’ti.**‘Now, Venerables, please go to one side for a moment while we discuss this matter.’*";
P_HTM[5701]="*Sace pana, bhikkhave, āvāsikā bhikkhū navakatarā honti, āgantukā bhikkhū vuḍḍhatarā, tehi, bhikkhave, āvāsikehi bhikkhūhi āgantukā bhikkhū evamassu vacanīyā—**If the visiting monks are senior to the resident monks, the resident monks should say,*";
P_HTM[5702]="*‘tena hi tumhe, āyasmanto, muhuttaṃ idheva tāva hotha, yāva mayaṃ mantemā’ti.**‘Well then, Venerables, please wait right here for a moment while we discuss this matter.’*";
P_HTM[5703]="*Sace pana, bhikkhave, āvāsikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ mantayamānānaṃ evaṃ hoti—**If, while discussing that matter, the resident monks think,*";
P_HTM[5704]="*‘na mayaṃ sakkoma imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ dhammena vinayena satthusāsanenā’ti, na taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ āvāsikehi bhikkhūhi sampaṭicchitabbaṃ.**‘We’re unable to resolve this legal issue according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction,’ then they should not take on that legal issue.*";
P_HTM[5705]="*Sace pana, bhikkhave, āvāsikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ mantayamānānaṃ evaṃ hoti—**But if they think,*";
P_HTM[5706]="*‘sakkoma mayaṃ imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ dhammena vinayena satthusāsanenā’ti.**‘We’re able to resolve this legal issue according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction,’*";
P_HTM[5707]="*Tehi, bhikkhave, āvāsikehi bhikkhūhi āgantukā bhikkhū evamassu vacanīyā—**then they should say to the visiting monks,*";
P_HTM[5708]="*‘sace tumhe, āyasmanto, amhākaṃ imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ yathājātaṃ yathāsamuppannaṃ ārocessatha, yathā ca mayaṃ imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasamessāma dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena tathā suvūpasantaṃ bhavissati.**‘If you will tell us how this legal issue arose, we’ll be able to resolve it properly according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction.*";
P_HTM[5709]="*Evaṃ mayaṃ imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ sampaṭicchissāma.**In this way we’ll take it on.*";
P_HTM[5710]="*No ce tumhe, āyasmanto, amhākaṃ imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ yathājātaṃ yathāsamuppannaṃ ārocessatha, yathā ca mayaṃ imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasamessāma dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena tathā na suvūpasantaṃ bhavissati, na mayaṃ imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ sampaṭicchissāmā’ti.**If, however, you won’t tell us how this legal issue arose, we won’t be able to resolve it properly according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction. We won’t take it on.’*";
P_HTM[5711]="*Evaṃ supariggahitaṃ kho, bhikkhave, katvā āvāsikehi bhikkhūhi taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ sampaṭicchitabbaṃ.**Dealing properly with the case in this way, the resident monks should take on that legal issue.*";
P_HTM[5712]="*Tehi, bhikkhave, āgantukehi bhikkhūhi āvāsikā bhikkhū evamassu vacanīyā—**The visiting monks should say this to the resident monks,*";
P_HTM[5713]="*‘yathājātaṃ yathāsamuppannaṃ mayaṃ imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ āyasmantānaṃ ārocessāma.**‘We’ll tell you how this legal issue arose.*";
P_HTM[5714]="*Sace āyasmantā sakkonti ettakena vā ettakena vā antarena imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena tathā suvūpasantaṃ bhavissati.**If you’re able to resolve this legal issue properly by such and such a deadline—according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction—*";
P_HTM[5715]="*Evaṃ mayaṃ imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ āyasmantānaṃ niyyādessāma.**then we’ll hand this legal issue over to you.*";
P_HTM[5716]="*No ce āyasmantā sakkonti ettakena vā ettakena vā antarena imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena tathā na suvūpasantaṃ bhavissati, na mayaṃ imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ āyasmantānaṃ niyyādessāma.**If you’re unable to resolve this legal issue properly by such and such a deadline—according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction—then we won’t hand this legal issue over to you.*";
P_HTM[5717]="*Mayameva imassa adhikaraṇassa sāmino bhavissāmā’ti.**We’ll take responsibility for this legal issue ourselves.’*";
P_HTM[5718]="*Evaṃ supariggahitaṃ kho, bhikkhave, katvā āgantukehi bhikkhūhi taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ āvāsikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ niyyādetabbaṃ.**Dealing properly with the case in this way, the visiting monks should hand that legal issue over to the resident monks.*";
P_HTM[5719]="*Te ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhū sakkonti taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ, idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasantaṃ.**If those monks are able to resolve that legal issue, this is called the resolution of a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[5720]="*Kena vūpasantaṃ?* **";
P_HTM[5721]="*Sammukhāvinayena.**It has been resolved face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[5722]="*Kiñca tattha sammukhāvinayasmiṃ?**Face-to-face with what?*";
P_HTM[5723]="*Saṅghasammukhatā, dhammasammukhatā, vinayasammukhatā, puggalasammukhatā …pe…**Face-to-face with the Sangha, face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law, face-to-face with the persons concerned. …*";
P_HTM[5724]="*evaṃ vūpasantañce, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ kārako ukkoṭeti, ukkoṭanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ;**When a legal issue has been resolved like this, if any of the participants reopen it, they incur an offense entailing confession for the reopening.*";
P_HTM[5725]="*chandadāyako khīyati, khīyanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If anyone who gave their consent criticizes the resolution, they incur an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5726]="*9.2. Ubbāhikāyavūpasamana**9.2 Resolution by committee*";
P_HTM[5727]="*Tehi ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhūhi tasmiṃ adhikaraṇe vinicchiyamāne anantāni ceva bhassāni jāyanti, na cekassa bhāsitassa attho viññāyati, anujānāmi, bhikkhave, evarūpaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ ubbāhikāya vūpasametuṃ.**“If, while they are deliberating, there is endless talk, but not a single statement that is clear, then they should resolve that legal issue by means of a committee.*";
P_HTM[5728]="*Dasahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya sammannitabbo—**A monk who has ten qualities may be appointed to that committee:*";
P_HTM[5729]="*sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati ācāragocarasampanno aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu;**One who is virtuous and restrained by the Monastic Code. His conduct is good, he associates with the right people, and he sees danger in minor faults. He undertakes and trains in the training rules.*";
P_HTM[5730]="*bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpassa dhammā bahussutā honti, dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā;**One who has learned much, and who retains and accumulates what he’s learned. Those teachings that are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, that have a true goal and are well articulated, and that set out the perfectly complete and pure spiritual life—he’s learned many such teachings, retained them in mind, recited them verbally, mentally investigated them, and penetrated them well by view.*";
P_HTM[5731]="*ubhayāni kho panassa pātimokkhāni vitthārena svāgatāni honti suvibhattāni suppavattīni suvinicchitāni suttaso anubyañjanaso;**One who has properly learned both Monastic Codes in detail; who has analyzed them well, thoroughly mastered them, and investigated them well, both in terms of the rules and their detailed exposition.*";
P_HTM[5732]="*vinaye kho pana ṭhito hoti asaṃhīro;**One who is firmly committed to the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[5733]="*paṭibalo hoti ubho atthapaccatthike assāsetuṃ saññāpetuṃ nijjhāpetuṃ pekkhetuṃ pasādetuṃ;**One who is capable of making both sides relax, of persuading them, of convincing them, of making them see, of reconciling them.*";
P_HTM[5734]="*adhikaraṇasamuppādavūpasamanakusalo hoti;**One who is knowledgeable about the arising and resolution of legal issues.*";
P_HTM[5735]="*adhikaraṇaṃ jānāti;**One who understands legal issues.*";
P_HTM[5736]="*adhikaraṇasamudayaṃ jānāti;**One who understands the arising of legal issues.*";
P_HTM[5737]="*adhikaraṇanirodhaṃ jānāti;**One who understands the ending of legal issues.*";
P_HTM[5738]="*adhikaraṇanirodhagāminipaṭipadaṃ jānāti.**One who understands the way to the ending of legal issues.*";
P_HTM[5739]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, imehi dasahaṅgehi samannāgataṃ bhikkhuṃ ubbāhikāya sammannituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5740]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sammannitabbo.**And he should be appointed like this.*";
P_HTM[5741]="*Paṭhamaṃ bhikkhu yācitabbo, yācitvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**First a monk should be asked, and then a competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[5742]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5743]="*Amhākaṃ imasmiṃ adhikaraṇe vinicchiyamāne anantāni ceva bhassāni jāyanti, na cekassa bhāsitassa attho viññāyati.**While we were deliberating, there was endless talk, but not a single statement that was clear.*";
P_HTM[5744]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmañca itthannāmañca bhikkhuṃ sammanneyya ubbāhikāya imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should appoint monk so-and-so and monk so-and-so to a committee to resolve this legal issue.*";
P_HTM[5745]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[5746]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5747]="*Amhākaṃ imasmiṃ adhikaraṇe vinicchiyamāne anantāni ceva bhassāni jāyanti, na cekassa bhāsitassa attho viññāyati.**While we were deliberating, there was endless talk, but not a single statement that was clear.*";
P_HTM[5748]="*Saṅgho itthannāmañca itthannāmañca bhikkhuṃ sammannati ubbāhikāya imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**The Sangha appoints monk so-and-so and monk so-and-so to a committee to resolve this legal issue.*";
P_HTM[5749]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa ca itthannāmassa ca bhikkhuno sammuti ubbāhikāya imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of appointing monk so-and-so and monk so-and-so to a committee should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[5750]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[5751]="*Sammato saṅghena itthannāmo ca itthannāmo ca bhikkhu ubbāhikāya imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**The Sangha has appointed monk so-and-so and monk so-and-so to a committee to resolve this legal issue.*";
P_HTM[5752]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[5753]="*Te ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhū sakkonti taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ ubbāhikāya vūpasametuṃ, idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasantaṃ.**If those monks are able to resolve that legal issue by committee, this is called the resolution of a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[5754]="*Kena vūpasantaṃ?* **";
P_HTM[5755]="*Sammukhāvinayena.**It has been resolved face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[5756]="*Kiñca tattha sammukhāvinayasmiṃ?**Face-to-face with what?*";
P_HTM[5757]="*Dhammasammukhatā, vinayasammukhatā, puggalasammukhatā …pe…**Face-to-face with the Sangha, face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law, face-to-face with the persons concerned. This is the meaning of face-to-face with the Sangha: the monks who should be present have arrived, consent has been brought for those who are eligible to give their consent, and no one present objects to the decision. This is the meaning of face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law: the Teaching, the Monastic Law, the Teacher’s instruction—that by which that legal issue is resolved. This is the meaning of face-to-face with the persons concerned: both sides—those who are disputing and those they are disputing with—are present.*";
P_HTM[5758]="*evaṃ vūpasantañce, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ kārako ukkoṭeti, ukkoṭanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**When a legal issue has been resolved like this, if any of the participants reopen it, they incur an offense entailing confession for the reopening.*";
P_HTM[5759]="*Tehi ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhūhi tasmiṃ adhikaraṇe vinicchiyamāne tatrāssa bhikkhu dhammakathiko, tassa neva suttaṃ āgataṃ hoti, no suttavibhaṅgo, so atthaṃ asallakkhento byañjanacchāyāya atthaṃ paṭibāhati, byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena te bhikkhū ñāpetabbā—**While those monks are deliberating on that legal issue, there may be a monk there who is an expounder of the Teaching. He doesn’t know the Monastic Code or its analysis. Not understanding the meaning, he blocks it out by covering it over with the wording. A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[5760]="*‘Suṇantu me āyasmantā.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask you to listen.*";
P_HTM[5761]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu dhammakathiko.**The monk so-and-so is an expounder of the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[5762]="*Imassa neva suttaṃ āgataṃ hoti, no suttavibhaṅgo.**He doesn’t know the Monastic Code or its analysis.*";
P_HTM[5763]="*So atthaṃ asallakkhento byañjanacchāyāya atthaṃ paṭibāhati.**Not understanding the meaning, he blocks it out by covering it over with the wording.*";
P_HTM[5764]="*Yadāyasmantānaṃ pattakallaṃ, itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā avasesā imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasameyyāmā’ti.**If it seems appropriate to the venerables, we should ask monk so-and-so to leave, and the remainder of us should resolve this legal issue.’*";
P_HTM[5765]="*Te ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhū taṃ bhikkhuṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā sakkonti taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ, idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasantaṃ.**If, after that monk has left, those monks are able to resolve that legal issue, this is called the resolution of a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[5766]="*Kena vūpasantaṃ?* **";
P_HTM[5767]="*Sammukhāvinayena.**It has been resolved face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[5768]="*Kiñca tattha sammukhāvinayasmiṃ?**Face-to-face with what?*";
P_HTM[5769]="*Dhammasammukhatā, vinayasammukhatā, puggalasammukhatā …pe…**Face-to-face with the Sangha, face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law, face-to-face with the persons concerned. …*";
P_HTM[5770]="*evaṃ vūpasantañce, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ kārako ukkoṭeti, ukkoṭanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**When a legal issue has been resolved like this, if any of the participants reopen it, they incur an offense entailing confession for the reopening.*";
P_HTM[5771]="*Tehi ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhūhi tasmiṃ adhikaraṇe vinicchiyamāne tatrāssa bhikkhu dhammakathiko, tassa suttañhi kho āgataṃ hoti, no suttavibhaṅgo, so atthaṃ asallakkhento byañjanacchāyāya atthaṃ paṭibāhati, byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena te bhikkhū ñāpetabbā—**While those monks are deliberating on that legal issue, there may be a monk there who is an expounder of the Teaching. He knows the Monastic Code, but not its analysis. Not understanding the meaning, he obstructs it by prioritizing the wording. A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[5772]="*‘Suṇantu me āyasmantā.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask you to listen.*";
P_HTM[5773]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu dhammakathiko.**The monk so-and-so is an expounder of the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[5774]="*Imassa suttañhi kho āgataṃ hoti, no suttavibhaṅgo.**He knows the Monastic Code, but not its analysis.*";
P_HTM[5775]="*So atthaṃ asallakkhento byañjanacchāyāya atthaṃ paṭibāhati.**Not understanding the meaning, he blocks it out by covering it over with the wording.*";
P_HTM[5776]="*Yadāyasmantānaṃ pattakallaṃ, itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā avasesā imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasameyyāmā’ti.**If it seems appropriate to the venerables, we should ask monk so-and-so to leave, and the remainder of us should resolve this legal issue.’*";
P_HTM[5777]="*Te ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhū taṃ bhikkhuṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā sakkonti taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ, idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasantaṃ.**If, after that monk has left, those monks are able to resolve that legal issue, this is called the resolution of a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[5778]="*Kena vūpasantaṃ?* **";
P_HTM[5779]="*Sammukhāvinayena.**It has been resolved face-to-face.*";
P_HTM[5780]="*Kiñca tattha sammukhāvinayasmiṃ?**Face-to-face with what?*";
P_HTM[5781]="*Dhammasammukhatā, vinayasammukhatā, puggalasammukhatā …pe…**Face-to-face with the Sangha, face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law, face-to-face with the persons concerned. …*";
P_HTM[5782]="*evaṃ vūpasantañce, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ kārako ukkoṭeti, ukkoṭanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**When a legal issue has been resolved like this, if any of the participants reopen it, they incur an offense entailing confession for the reopening.*";
P_HTM[5783]="*9.3. Yebhuyyasikāvinaya**9.3 Resolution by majority decision*";
P_HTM[5784]="*Te ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhū na sakkonti taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ ubbāhikāya vūpasametuṃ, tehi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūhi taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ saṅghassa niyyādetabbaṃ—**“If those monks are unable to resolve that legal issue by committee, they should hand it over to the Sangha, saying,*";
P_HTM[5785]="*‘na mayaṃ, bhante, sakkoma imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ ubbāhikāya vūpasametuṃ, saṅghova imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametū’ti.**‘Venerables, we’re unable to resolve this legal issue by committee. May the Sangha resolve this legal issue.’*";
P_HTM[5786]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, evarūpaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ yebhuyyasikāya vūpasametuṃ.**I allow such a legal issue to be resolved by majority decision.*";
P_HTM[5787]="*Pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu salākaggāhāpako sammannitabbo—**A monk who has five qualities should be appointed as the manager of the vote:*";
P_HTM[5788]="*yo na chandāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na dosāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na mohāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na bhayāgatiṃ gaccheyya, gahitāgahitañca jāneyya …pe…**one who isn’t swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear, and who knows who has and has not voted.*";
P_HTM[5789]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, sammannitabbo.**And he should be appointed like this.*";
P_HTM[5790]="*Paṭhamaṃ bhikkhu yācitabbo, yācitvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**First a monk should be asked, and then a competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[5791]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5792]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ salākaggāhāpakaṃ sammanneyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should appoint monk so-and-so as the manager of the vote.*";
P_HTM[5793]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[5794]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5795]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ salākaggāhāpakaṃ sammannati.**The Sangha appoints monk so-and-so as the manager of the vote*";
P_HTM[5796]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno salākaggāhāpakassa sammuti, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of appointing monk so-and-so as the manager of the vote should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[5797]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[5798]="*Sammato saṅghena itthannāmo bhikkhu salākaggāhāpako.**The Sangha has appointed monk so-and-so as the manager of the vote.*";
P_HTM[5799]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[5800]="*Tena salākaggāhāpakena bhikkhunā salākā gāhetabbā.**That monk should then distribute the voting tickets.*";
P_HTM[5801]="*Yathā bahutarā bhikkhū dhammavādino vadanti tathā taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametabbaṃ.**If the majority of monks vote in accordance with the Teaching, then that legal issue has been resolved.*";
P_HTM[5802]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasantaṃ.**This is called the resolution of a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[5803]="*Kena vūpasantaṃ?* **";
P_HTM[5804]="*Sammukhāvinayena ca, yebhuyyasikāya ca.**It has been resolved face-to-face and by majority decision.*";
P_HTM[5805]="*Kiñca tattha sammukhāvinayasmiṃ?**Face-to-face with what?*";
P_HTM[5806]="*Saṅghasammukhatā, dhammasammukhatā, vinayasammukhatā, puggalasammukhatā.**Face-to-face with the Sangha, face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law, face-to-face with the persons concerned.*";
P_HTM[5807]="*Kā ca tattha saṅghasammukhatā?**This is the meaning of face-to-face with the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[5808]="*Yāvatikā bhikkhū kammappattā te āgatā honti, chandārahānaṃ chando āhaṭo hoti, sammukhībhūtā na paṭikkosanti—**the monks who should be present have arrived, consent has been brought for those who are eligible to give their consent, and no one present objects to the decision.*";
P_HTM[5809]="*ayaṃ tattha saṅghasammukhatā.* **";
P_HTM[5810]="*Kā ca tattha dhammasammukhatā, vinayasammukhatā?**This is the meaning of face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law:*";
P_HTM[5811]="*Yena dhammena yena vinayena yena satthusāsanena taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati—**the Teaching, the Monastic Law, the Teacher’s instruction—that by which that legal issue is resolved.*";
P_HTM[5812]="*ayaṃ tattha dhammasammukhatā, vinayasammukhatā.* **";
P_HTM[5813]="*Kā ca tattha puggalasammukhatā?**This is the meaning of face-to-face with the persons concerned:*";
P_HTM[5814]="*Yo ca vivadati, yena ca vivadati, ubho atthapaccatthikā sammukhībhūtā honti—**both sides—those who are disputing and those they are disputing with—are present.*";
P_HTM[5815]="*ayaṃ tattha puggalasammukhatā.* **";
P_HTM[5816]="*Kā ca tattha yebhuyyasikāya?**This is the meaning of majority decision:*";
P_HTM[5817]="*Yā yebhuyyasikākammassa kiriyā karaṇaṃ upagamanaṃ ajjhupagamanaṃ adhivāsanā appaṭikkosanā—**the doing of, the performing of, the participation in, the consent to, the agreement to, the non-objection to that legal procedure of majority decision.*";
P_HTM[5818]="*ayaṃ tattha yebhuyyasikāya.* **";
P_HTM[5819]="*Evaṃ vūpasantañce, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ kārako ukkoṭeti, ukkoṭanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ;**When a legal issue has been resolved like this, if any of the participants reopen it, they incur an offense entailing confession for the reopening.*";
P_HTM[5820]="*chandadāyako khīyati, khīyanakaṃ pācittiyan”ti.**If anyone who gave their consent criticizes the resolution, they incur an offense entailing confession.”*";
P_HTM[5821]="*9.4. Tividhasalākaggāha**9.4 The three kinds of voting*";
P_HTM[5822]="*Tena kho pana samayena sāvatthiyā evaṃ jātaṃ evaṃ samuppannaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ hoti.**At one time at Sāvatthī a legal issue had arisen in this way.*";
P_HTM[5823]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū—**But those monks*";
P_HTM[5824]="*asantuṭṭhā sāvatthiyā saṅghassa adhikaraṇavūpasamanena—**were dissatisfied with how the Sangha at Sāvatthī had resolved that legal issue.*";
P_HTM[5825]="*assosuṃ kho amukasmiṃ kira āvāse sambahulā therā viharanti bahussutā āgatāgamā dhammadharā vinayadharā mātikādharā paṇḍitā viyattā medhāvino lajjino kukkuccakā sikkhākāmā.**They heard that in a certain monastery there was a number of senior monks who were learned and masters of the tradition; who were experts on the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the summaries; who were knowledgeable and competent, had a sense of conscience, and were afraid of wrongdoing and fond of the training.*";
P_HTM[5826]="*Te ce therā imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasameyyuṃ dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena, evamidaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ suvūpasantaṃ assāti.**They thought, “If these senior monks resolve this legal issue—according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction—then it will be properly resolved.”*";
P_HTM[5827]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū taṃ āvāsaṃ gantvā te there etadavocuṃ—**They then went to that monastery and said to those senior monks,*";
P_HTM[5828]="*“idaṃ, bhante, adhikaraṇaṃ evaṃ jātaṃ, evaṃ samuppannaṃ.**“This legal issue has arisen in this way.*";
P_HTM[5829]="*Sādhu, bhante, therā imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasamentu dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena, yathayidaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ suvūpasantaṃ assā”ti.**It would be good, Venerables, if you would resolve it—according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction—so that it will be properly resolved.”*";
P_HTM[5830]="*Atha kho te therā—**Those senior monks thought,*";
P_HTM[5831]="*yathā sāvatthiyā saṅghena adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasamitaṃ tathā suvūpasantanti—**“This legal issue was properly resolved by the Sangha at Sāvatthī,”*";
P_HTM[5832]="*tathā taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasamesuṃ.**and they resolved it in the same way.*";
P_HTM[5833]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū—**Those monks*";
P_HTM[5834]="*asantuṭṭhā sāvatthiyā saṅghassa adhikaraṇavūpasamanena, asantuṭṭhā sambahulānaṃ therānaṃ adhikaraṇavūpasamanena—**were dissatisfied with how the Sangha at Sāvatthī had resolved that legal issue and also with how that number of senior monks had resolved it.*";
P_HTM[5835]="*assosuṃ kho amukasmiṃ kira āvāse tayo therā viharanti …pe…**But they heard that in a certain monastery there were three senior monks …*";
P_HTM[5836]="*dve therā viharanti …pe…**two senior monks …*";
P_HTM[5837]="*eko thero viharati bahussuto āgatāgamo dhammadharo vinayadharo mātikādharo paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī lajjī kukkuccako sikkhākāmo.**one senior monk who was learned and a master of the tradition; who was an expert on the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the summaries; who was knowledgeable and competent, had a sense of conscience, and was afraid of wrongdoing and fond of the training.*";
P_HTM[5838]="*So ce thero imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasameyya dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena, evamidaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ suvūpasantaṃ assāti.**They thought, “If this senior monk resolves this legal issue—according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction—then it will be properly resolved.”*";
P_HTM[5839]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū taṃ āvāsaṃ gantvā taṃ theraṃ etadavocuṃ—**They then went to that monastery and said to that senior monk,*";
P_HTM[5840]="*“idaṃ, bhante, adhikaraṇaṃ evaṃ jātaṃ, evaṃ samuppannaṃ.**“This legal issue has arisen in this way.*";
P_HTM[5841]="*Sādhu, bhante, thero imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametu dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena, yathayidaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ suvūpasantaṃ assā”ti.**It would be good, Venerable, if you would resolve it—according to the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction—so that it will be properly resolved.”*";
P_HTM[5842]="*Atha kho so thero—**That senior monk thought,*";
P_HTM[5843]="*yathā sāvatthiyā saṅghena adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasamitaṃ, yathā sambahulehi therehi adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasamitaṃ, yathā tīhi therehi adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasamitaṃ, yathā dvīhi therehi adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasamitaṃ, tathā suvūpasantanti—**“This legal issue was properly resolved by the Sangha at Sāvatthī, and likewise by that number of senior monks, by those three senior monks, and by those two senior monks,”*";
P_HTM[5844]="*tathā taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasamesi.**and he resolved it in the same way.*";
P_HTM[5845]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū asantuṭṭhā sāvatthiyā saṅghassa adhikaraṇavūpasamanena, asantuṭṭhā sambahulānaṃ therānaṃ adhikaraṇavūpasamanena, asantuṭṭhā tiṇṇaṃ therānaṃ adhikaraṇavūpasamanena, asantuṭṭhā dvinnaṃ therānaṃ adhikaraṇavūpasamanena, asantuṭṭhā ekassa therassa adhikaraṇavūpasamanena, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**Since those monks were dissatisfied with how all of these had resolved that legal issue, they went to the Buddha and told him what had happened. …*";
P_HTM[5846]="*“Nihatametaṃ, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ santaṃ vūpasantaṃ suvūpasantaṃ.**The Buddha said, “Monks, this legal issue has been settled, laid to rest, and properly resolved.*";
P_HTM[5847]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ saññattiyā tayo salākaggāhe—**To persuade those monks, I allow three kinds of voting:*";
P_HTM[5848]="*gūḷhakaṃ, sakaṇṇajappakaṃ, vivaṭakaṃ.**a secret one, one by whispering in the ear, and an open vote.*";
P_HTM[5849]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, gūḷhako salākaggāho hoti?**What is a secret vote?*";
P_HTM[5850]="*Tena salākaggāhāpakena bhikkhunā salākāyo vaṇṇāvaṇṇāyo katvā ekameko bhikkhu upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo—**The manager of the vote should make voting tickets of two different colors, go up to the monks one by one and say,*";
P_HTM[5851]="*‘ayaṃ evaṃvādissa salākā, ayaṃ evaṃvādissa salākā.**‘This is the voting ticket for those who hold this view, and this is the voting ticket for those who hold that view.*";
P_HTM[5852]="*Yaṃ icchasi taṃ gaṇhāhī’ti.**Take the one you like.’*";
P_HTM[5853]="*Gahite vattabbo—**When someone has taken a voting ticket, he should be told,*";
P_HTM[5854]="*‘mā ca kassaci dassehī’ti.**‘Don’t show it to anyone.’*";
P_HTM[5855]="*Sace jānāti—**If the manager knows that*";
P_HTM[5856]="*adhammavādī bahutarāti, duggahoti, paccukkaḍḍhitabbaṃ.**those who speak contrary to the Teaching are in the majority, then that vote is invalid and to be postponed.*";
P_HTM[5857]="*Sace jānāti—**If he knows that*";
P_HTM[5858]="*dhammavādī bahutarāti, suggahoti, sāvetabbaṃ.**those who speak in accordance with the Teaching are in the majority, then that vote is valid and is to be announced.*";
P_HTM[5859]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, gūḷhako salākaggāho hoti.* **";
P_HTM[5860]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, sakaṇṇajappako salākaggāho hoti?**What is a vote by whispering in the ear?*";
P_HTM[5861]="*Tena salākaggāhāpakena bhikkhunā ekamekassa bhikkhuno upakaṇṇake ārocetabbaṃ—**The manager of the vote should inform the monks one by one by whispering in the ear,*";
P_HTM[5862]="*‘ayaṃ evaṃvādissa salākā, ayaṃ evaṃvādissa salākā.**‘This is the voting ticket for those who hold this view, and this is the voting ticket for those who hold that view.*";
P_HTM[5863]="*Yaṃ icchasi taṃ gaṇhāhī’ti.**Take the one you like.’*";
P_HTM[5864]="*Gahite vattabbo—**When someone has taken a voting ticket, he should be told,*";
P_HTM[5865]="*‘mā ca kassaci ārocehī’ti.**‘Don’t tell anyone.’*";
P_HTM[5866]="*Sace jānāti—**If the manager knows that*";
P_HTM[5867]="*adhammavādī bahutarāti, duggahoti, paccukkaḍḍhitabbaṃ.**those who speak contrary to the Teaching are in the majority, then that vote is invalid and to be postponed.*";
P_HTM[5868]="*Sace jānāti—**If he knows that*";
P_HTM[5869]="*dhammavādī bahutarāti, suggahoti, sāvetabbaṃ.**those who speak in accordance with the Teaching are in the majority, then that vote is valid and is to be announced.*";
P_HTM[5870]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, sakaṇṇajappako salākaggāho hoti.* **";
P_HTM[5871]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, vivaṭako salākaggāho hoti?**What is an open vote?*";
P_HTM[5872]="*Sace jānāti—**If he knows that*";
P_HTM[5873]="*dhammavādī bahutarāti, vissaṭṭheneva vivaṭena gāhetabbo.**those who speak in accordance with the Teaching are in the majority, the voting tickets should be distributed openly.”*";
P_HTM[5874]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, vivaṭako salākaggāho hoti.* **";
P_HTM[5875]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo salākaggāhā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5876]="*9.5. Sativinaya**9.5 Resolution through recollection*";
P_HTM[5877]="*“Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ katihi samathehi sammati?* **";
P_HTM[5878]="*Anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ catūhi samathehi sammati—**“There are four principles for settling a legal issue arising from an accusation:*";
P_HTM[5879]="*sammukhāvinayena ca, sativinayena ca, amūḷhavinayena ca, tassapāpiyasikāya ca.**resolution face-to-face, resolution through recollection, resolution because of past insanity, and by further penalty.*";
P_HTM[5880]="*Siyā anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ dve samathe anāgamma—**Can it be that a legal issue arising from an accusation should be settled*";
P_HTM[5881]="*amūḷhavinayañca, tassapāpiyasikañca;**not by resolution because of past insanity or by further penalty,*";
P_HTM[5882]="*dvīhi samathehi sammeyya—**but*";
P_HTM[5883]="*sammukhāvinayena ca, sativinayena cāti?**by resolution face-to-face and by resolution through recollection?*";
P_HTM[5884]="*Siyātissa vacanīyaṃ.**It can.*";
P_HTM[5885]="*Yathā kathaṃ viya?**How is that?*";
P_HTM[5886]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhū bhikkhuṃ amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā anuddhaṃsenti.**It may be that monks are groundlessly charging a monk with failure in morality.*";
P_HTM[5887]="*Tassa kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno sativepullappattassa sativinayo dātabbo.**If that monk has great clarity of memory, he is to be granted resolution through recollection.*";
P_HTM[5888]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbo—**And it should be granted like this:*";
P_HTM[5889]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā …pe…**That monk should approach the Sangha, put his upper robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms,*";
P_HTM[5890]="*evamassa vacanīyo—**and say:*";
P_HTM[5891]="*‘maṃ, bhante, bhikkhū amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā anuddhaṃsenti.**‘Venerables, monks are groundlessly charging me with failure in morality.*";
P_HTM[5892]="*Sohaṃ, bhante, sativepullappatto saṅghaṃ sativinayaṃ yācāmī’ti.**Because of my great clarity of memory, I ask the Sangha for resolution through recollection.’*";
P_HTM[5893]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbo.**And he should ask a second*";
P_HTM[5894]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbo.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[5895]="*Byattenaṃ bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[5896]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5897]="*Bhikkhū itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā anuddhaṃsenti.**Monks are groundlessly charging monk so-and-so with failure in morality.*";
P_HTM[5898]="*So sativepullappatto saṅghaṃ sativinayaṃ yācati.**Because of his great clarity of memory, he is asking the Sangha for resolution through recollection.*";
P_HTM[5899]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno sativepullappattassa sativinayaṃ dadeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should grant him resolution through recollection.*";
P_HTM[5900]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[5901]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5902]="*Bhikkhū itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā anuddhaṃsenti.**Monks are groundlessly charging monk so-and-so with failure in morality.*";
P_HTM[5903]="*So sativepullappatto saṅghaṃ sativinayaṃ yācati.**Because of his great clarity of memory, he is asking the Sangha for resolution through recollection.*";
P_HTM[5904]="*Saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno sativepullappattassa sativinayaṃ deti.**The Sangha grants him resolution through recollection.*";
P_HTM[5905]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno sativepullappattassa sativinayassa dānaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of granting him resolution through recollection should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[5906]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[5907]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[5908]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe….**For the third time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[5909]="*Dinno saṅghena itthannāmassa bhikkhuno sativepullappattassa sativinayo.**Because of his great clarity of memory, the Sangha has granted monk so-and-so resolution through recollection.*";
P_HTM[5910]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[5911]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasantaṃ.**This is called the resolution of a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[5912]="*Kena vūpasantaṃ?* **";
P_HTM[5913]="*Sammukhāvinayena ca sativinayena ca.**It has been resolved by resolution face-to-face and by resolution through recollection.*";
P_HTM[5914]="*Kiñca tattha sammukhāvinayasmiṃ?**Face-to-face with what?*";
P_HTM[5915]="*Saṅghasammukhatā, dhammasammukhatā, vinayasammukhatā, puggalasammukhatā …pe…**Face-to-face with the Sangha, face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law, face-to-face with the persons concerned. This is the meaning of face-to-face with the Sangha: the monks who should be present have arrived, consent has been brought for those who are eligible to give their consent, and no one present objects to the decision. This is the meaning of face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law: the Teaching, the Monastic Law, the Teacher’s instruction—that by which that legal issue is resolved.*";
P_HTM[5916]="*kā ca tattha puggalasammukhatā?**This is the meaning of face-to-face with the persons concerned:*";
P_HTM[5917]="*Yo ca anuvadati, yañca anuvadati, ubho sammukhībhūtā honti—**both those who are accusing and those who have been accused are present.*";
P_HTM[5918]="*ayaṃ tattha puggalasammukhatā.* **";
P_HTM[5919]="*Kiñca tattha sativinayasmiṃ?**This is the meaning of resolution through recollection:*";
P_HTM[5920]="*Yā sativinayassa kammassa kiriyā karaṇaṃ upagamanaṃ ajjhupagamanaṃ adhivāsanā appaṭikkosanā—**the doing of, the performing of, the participation in, the consent to, the agreement to, the non-objection to that legal procedure of resolution through recollection.*";
P_HTM[5921]="*idaṃ tattha sativinayasmiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5922]="*Evaṃ vūpasantañce, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ kārako ukkoṭeti, ukkoṭanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ;**When a legal issue has been resolved like this, if any of the participants reopen it, they incur an offense entailing confession for the reopening.*";
P_HTM[5923]="*chandadāyako khīyati, khīyanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If anyone who gave their consent criticizes the resolution, they incur an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5924]="*9.6. Amūḷhavinaya**9.6 Resolution because of past insanity*";
P_HTM[5925]="*Siyā anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ dve samathe anāgamma—**“Can it be that a legal issue arising from an accusation should be settled*";
P_HTM[5926]="*sativinayañca, tassapāpiyasikañca;**not by resolution through recollection or by further penalty,*";
P_HTM[5927]="*dvīhi samathehi sammeyya—**but*";
P_HTM[5928]="*sammukhāvinayena ca, amūḷhavinayena cāti?**by resolution face-to-face and by resolution because of past insanity?*";
P_HTM[5929]="*Siyātissa vacanīyaṃ.**It can.*";
P_HTM[5930]="*Yathā kathaṃ viya?**How is that?*";
P_HTM[5931]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ummattako hoti cittavipariyāsakato.**It may be that a monk is insane and suffering from psychosis.*";
P_HTM[5932]="*Tena ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ hoti bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**Because of that, he does and says many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5933]="*Taṃ bhikkhū ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena ajjhāciṇṇena āpattiyā codenti—**Monks accuse him of an offense, saying,*";
P_HTM[5934]="*‘saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā’ti.**‘Venerable, do you remember committing such-and-such an offense?’*";
P_HTM[5935]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**He replies,*";
P_HTM[5936]="*‘ahaṃ kho, āvuso, ummattako ahosiṃ cittavipariyāsakato.**‘I was insane and suffering from psychosis.*";
P_HTM[5937]="*Tena me ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**Because of that, I did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5938]="*Nāhaṃ taṃ sarāmi.**I don’t remember it;*";
P_HTM[5939]="*Mūḷhena me etaṃ katan’ti.**I did it because I was insane.’*";
P_HTM[5940]="*Evampi naṃ vuccamānā codenteva—**But they still accused him*";
P_HTM[5941]="*‘saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā’ti.**in the same way.*";
P_HTM[5942]="*Tassa kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno amūḷhassa amūḷhavinayo dātabbo.**If he is no longer insane, that monk should be granted resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[5943]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbo—**And it should be granted like this:*";
P_HTM[5944]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā …pe…**That monk should approach the Sangha, put his upper robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms,*";
P_HTM[5945]="*evamassa vacanīyo—**and say:*";
P_HTM[5946]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, ummattako ahosiṃ cittavipariyāsakato.**‘Venerables, I have been insane and suffering from psychosis.*";
P_HTM[5947]="*Tena me ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**Because of that, I did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5948]="*Maṃ bhikkhū ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena ajjhāciṇṇena āpattiyā codenti—**Monks accused me of an offense, saying,*";
P_HTM[5949]="*“saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā”ti.**“Venerable, do you remember committing such-and-such an offense?”*";
P_HTM[5950]="*Tyāhaṃ evaṃ vadāmi—**I replied,*";
P_HTM[5951]="*“ahaṃ kho, āvuso, ummattako ahosiṃ cittavipariyāsakato.**“I was insane and suffering from psychosis.*";
P_HTM[5952]="*Tena me ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**Because of that, I did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5953]="*Nāhaṃ taṃ sarāmi.**I don’t remember it;*";
P_HTM[5954]="*Mūḷhena me etaṃ katan”ti.**I did it because I was insane.”*";
P_HTM[5955]="*Evampi maṃ vuccamānā codenteva—**But they still accused me*";
P_HTM[5956]="*“saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā”ti.**in the same way.*";
P_HTM[5957]="*“Sohaṃ, bhante, amūḷho saṅghaṃ amūḷhavinayaṃ yācāmī”’ti.**Because I’m no longer insane, I ask the Sangha for resolution because of past insanity.’*";
P_HTM[5958]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbo.**And he should ask a second*";
P_HTM[5959]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbo.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[5960]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[5961]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5962]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu ummattako ahosi cittavipariyāsakato.**The monk so-and-so has been insane and suffering from psychosis.*";
P_HTM[5963]="*Tena ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**Because of that, he did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5964]="*Taṃ bhikkhū ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena ajjhāciṇṇena āpattiyā codenti—**Monks accused him of an offense, saying,*";
P_HTM[5965]="*“saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā”ti.**“Venerable, do you remember committing such-and-such an offense?”*";
P_HTM[5966]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**He replied,*";
P_HTM[5967]="*“ahaṃ kho, āvuso, ummattako ahosiṃ cittavipariyāsakato.**“I was insane and suffering from psychosis.*";
P_HTM[5968]="*Tena me ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**Because of that, I did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
