P_HTM[5970]="*Mūḷhena me etaṃ katan”ti.**I did it because I was insane.”*";
P_HTM[5971]="*Evampi naṃ vuccamānā codenteva—**But they still accused him*";
P_HTM[5972]="*“saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā”ti.**in the same way.*";
P_HTM[5973]="*So amūḷho saṅghaṃ amūḷhavinayaṃ yācati.**Because he is no longer insane, he is asking the Sangha for resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[5974]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno amūḷhassa amūḷhavinayaṃ dadeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should grant him resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[5975]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[5976]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5977]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu ummattako ahosi cittavipariyāsakato.**The monk so-and-so has been insane and suffering from psychosis.*";
P_HTM[5978]="*Tena ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**Because of that, he did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5979]="*Taṃ bhikkhū ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena ajjhāciṇṇena āpattiyā codenti—**Monks accused him of an offense, saying,*";
P_HTM[5980]="*“saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā”ti.**“Venerable, do you remember committing such-and-such an offense?”*";
P_HTM[5981]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**He replied,*";
P_HTM[5982]="*“ahaṃ kho, āvuso, ummattako ahosiṃ cittavipariyāsakato.**“I was insane and suffering from psychosis.*";
P_HTM[5983]="*Tena me ummattakena cittavipariyāsakatena bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**Because of that, I did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[5984]="*Nāhaṃ taṃ sarāmi.**I don’t remember it;*";
P_HTM[5985]="*Mūḷhena me etaṃ katan”ti.**I did it because I was insane.”*";
P_HTM[5986]="*Evampi naṃ vuccamānā codenteva—**But they still accused him*";
P_HTM[5987]="*“saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā”ti.**in the same way.*";
P_HTM[5988]="*So amūḷho saṅghaṃ amūḷhavinayaṃ yācati.**Because he is no longer insane, he is asking the Sangha for resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[5989]="*Saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno amūḷhassa amūḷhavinayaṃ deti.**The Sangha grants him resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[5990]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno amūḷhassa amūḷhavinayassa dānaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of granting him resolution because of past insanity should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[5991]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[5992]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[5993]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe….**For the third time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[5994]="*Dinno saṅghena itthannāmassa bhikkhuno amūḷhassa amūḷhavinayo.**Because he is no longer insane, the Sangha has granted monk so-and-so resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[5995]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[5996]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasantaṃ.**This is called the resolution of a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[5997]="*Kena vūpasantaṃ?* **";
P_HTM[5998]="*Sammukhāvinayena ca, amūḷhavinayena ca.**It has been resolved by resolution face-to-face and by resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[5999]="*Kiñca tattha sammukhāvinayasmiṃ?**Face-to-face with what?*";
P_HTM[6000]="*Saṅghasammukhatā, dhammasammukhatā, vinayasammukhatā, puggalasammukhatā …pe…**Face-to-face with the Sangha, face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law, face-to-face with the persons concerned. This is the meaning of face-to-face with the Sangha: the monks who should be present have arrived, consent has been brought for those who are eligible to give their consent, and no one present objects to the decision. This is the meaning of face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law: the Teaching, the Monastic Law, the Teacher’s instruction—that by which that legal issue is resolved. This is the meaning of face-to-face with the persons concerned: both those who are accusing and those who have been accused are present.*";
P_HTM[6001]="*kiñca tattha amūḷhavinayasmiṃ?**This is the meaning of resolution because of past insanity:*";
P_HTM[6002]="*Yā amūḷhavinayassa kammassa kiriyā karaṇaṃ upagamanaṃ ajjhupagamanaṃ adhivāsanā appaṭikkosanā—**the doing of, the performing of, the participation in, the consent to, the agreement to, the non-objection to that legal procedure of resolution because of past insanity.*";
P_HTM[6003]="*idaṃ tattha amūḷhavinayasmiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6004]="*Evaṃ vūpasantañce, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ kārako ukkoṭeti, ukkoṭanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ;**When a legal issue has been resolved like this, if any of the participants reopen it, they incur an offense entailing confession for the reopening.*";
P_HTM[6005]="*chandadāyako khīyati, khīyanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If anyone who gave their consent criticizes the resolution, they incur an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6006]="*9.7. Tassapāpiyasikāvinaya**9.7 Resolution by further penalty*";
P_HTM[6007]="*Siyā anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ dve samathe anāgamma—**“Can it be that a legal issue arising from an accusation should be settled*";
P_HTM[6008]="*sativinayañca, amūḷhavinayañca;**not by resolution through recollection or by resolution because of past insanity,*";
P_HTM[6009]="*dvīhi samathehi sammeyya—**but*";
P_HTM[6010]="*sammukhāvinayena ca, tassapāpiyasikāya cāti?**by resolution face-to-face and by further penalty?*";
P_HTM[6011]="*Siyātissa vacanīyaṃ.**It can.*";
P_HTM[6012]="*Yathā kathaṃ viya?**How is that?*";
P_HTM[6013]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ saṅghamajjhe garukāya āpattiyā codeti—**It may be that a monk accuses a monk of an offense in the midst of the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[6014]="*‘saratāyasmā evarūpiṃ garukaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā, pārājikaṃ vā pārājikasāmantaṃ vā’ti.**‘Venerable, do you remember committing such-and-such a heavy offense entailing expulsion or bordering on expulsion?’*";
P_HTM[6015]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**He replies,*";
P_HTM[6016]="*‘na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, sarāmi evarūpiṃ garukaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā, pārājikaṃ vā pārājikasāmantaṃ vā’ti.**‘I don’t.’*";
P_HTM[6017]="*Tamenaṃ so nibbeṭhentaṃ ativeṭheti—**As he tries to free himself, the accusing monk presses him further:*";
P_HTM[6018]="*‘iṅghāyasmā sādhukameva jānāhi, yadi sarasi evarūpiṃ garukaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā, pārājikaṃ vā pārājikasāmantaṃ vā’ti.**‘Come on, Venerable, think properly whether you remember committing such-and-such a heavy offense.’*";
P_HTM[6019]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**He replies,*";
P_HTM[6020]="*‘na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, sarāmi evarūpiṃ garukaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā, pārājikaṃ vā pārājikasāmantaṃ vā.**‘I don’t remember committing a heavy offense.*";
P_HTM[6021]="*Sarāmi ca kho ahaṃ, āvuso, evarūpiṃ appamattikaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā’ti.**But I do remember committing such-and-such a minor offense.’*";
P_HTM[6022]="*Tamenaṃ so nibbeṭhentaṃ ativeṭheti—**As he tries to free himself, the accusing monk presses him further:*";
P_HTM[6023]="*‘iṅghāyasmā sādhukameva jānāhi, yadi sarasi evarūpiṃ garukaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā, pārājikaṃ vā pārājikasāmantaṃ vā’ti.**‘Come on, Venerable, think properly whether you remember committing such-and-such a heavy offense.’*";
P_HTM[6024]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**He replies,*";
P_HTM[6025]="*‘imañhi nāmāhaṃ, āvuso, appamattikaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitvā apuṭṭho paṭijānissāmi.**‘I have admitted that I’ve committed this minor offense without being asked.*";
P_HTM[6026]="*Kiṃ panāhaṃ evarūpiṃ garukaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitvā, pārājikaṃ vā pārājikasāmantaṃ vā, puṭṭho na paṭijānissāmī’ti?**So when asked about such-and-such a heavy offense, why would I not admit it?’*";
P_HTM[6027]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**The accusing monk says,*";
P_HTM[6028]="*‘imañhi nāma tvaṃ, āvuso, appamattikaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitvā apuṭṭho na paṭijānissasi.**‘But you didn’t admit that you had committed this minor offense without being asked.*";
P_HTM[6029]="*Kiṃ pana tvaṃ evarūpiṃ garukaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitvā, pārājikaṃ vā pārājikasāmantaṃ vā, apuṭṭho paṭijānissasi?**So when asked about such-and-such a heavy offense, why would you admit it?*";
P_HTM[6030]="*Iṅghāyasmā sādhukameva jānāhi, yadi sarasi evarūpiṃ garukaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā, pārājikaṃ vā pārājikasāmantaṃ vā’ti.**Come on, Venerable, think properly whether you remember committing such-and-such a heavy offense.’*";
P_HTM[6031]="*So evaṃ vadesi—**He then says,*";
P_HTM[6032]="*‘sarāmi kho ahaṃ, āvuso, evarūpiṃ garukaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā, pārājikaṃ vā pārājikasāmantaṃ vā.**‘I remember committing such-and-such a heavy offense entailing expulsion or bordering on expulsion.*";
P_HTM[6033]="*Davā me etaṃ vuttaṃ, ravā me etaṃ vuttaṃ—**When I said that I didn’t remember, I spoke playfully, I spoke too fast.’*";
P_HTM[6034]="*nāhaṃ taṃ sarāmi evarūpiṃ garukaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitā, pārājikaṃ vā pārājikasāmantaṃ vā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6035]="*Tassa kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**They should do a legal procedure of further penalty against that monk.*";
P_HTM[6036]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, kātabbaṃ.**And it should be done like this.*";
P_HTM[6037]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[6038]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[6039]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu saṅghamajjhe garukāya āpattiyā anuyuñjiyamāno avajānitvā paṭijānāti, paṭijānitvā avajānāti, aññenāññaṃ paṭicarati, sampajānamusā bhāsati.**The monk so-and-so, while being examined in the midst of the Sangha about a heavy offense, asserts things after denying them, denies things after asserting them, evades the issue, and lies.*";
P_HTM[6040]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ kareyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should do a legal procedure of further penalty against this monk.*";
P_HTM[6041]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[6042]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[6043]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu saṅghamajjhe garukāya āpattiyā anuyuñjiyamāno avajānitvā paṭijānāti, paṭijānitvā avajānāti, aññenāññaṃ paṭicarati, sampajānamusā bhāsati.**The monk so-and-so, while being examined in the midst of the Sangha about a heavy offense, asserts things after denying them, denies things after asserting them, evades the issue, and lies.*";
P_HTM[6044]="*Saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ karoti.**The Sangha does a legal procedure of further penalty against this monk.*";
P_HTM[6045]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno tassapāpiyasikākammassa karaṇaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of doing a legal procedure of further penalty against this monk should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[6046]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[6047]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[6048]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe….**For the third time I speak on this matter. …*";
P_HTM[6049]="*Kataṃ saṅghena itthannāmassa bhikkhuno tassapāpiyasikākammaṃ.**The Sangha has done a legal procedure of further penalty against this monk.*";
P_HTM[6050]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[6051]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasantaṃ.**This is called the resolution of a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[6052]="*Kena vūpasantaṃ?* **";
P_HTM[6053]="*Sammukhāvinayena ca, tassapāpiyasikāya ca.**It has been resolved face-to-face and by further penalty.*";
P_HTM[6054]="*Kiñca tattha sammukhāvinayasmiṃ?**Face-to-face with what?*";
P_HTM[6055]="*Saṅghasammukhatā, dhammasammukhatā, vinayasammukhatā …pe…**Face-to-face with the Sangha, face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law, face-to-face with the persons concerned. This is the meaning of face-to-face with the Sangha: the monks who should be present have arrived, consent has been brought for those who are eligible to give their consent, and no one present objects to the decision. This is the meaning of face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law: the Teaching, the Monastic Law, the Teacher’s instruction—that by which that legal issue is resolved. This is the meaning of face-to-face with the persons concerned: both those who are accusing and those who have been accused are present.*";
P_HTM[6056]="*kā ca tattha tassapāpiyasikāya?**This is the meaning of further penalty:*";
P_HTM[6057]="*Yā tassapāpiyasikākammassa kiriyā karaṇaṃ upagamanaṃ ajjhupagamanaṃ adhivāsanā appaṭikkosanā—**the doing of, the performing of, the participation in, the consent to, the agreement to, the non-objection to that legal procedure of further penalty.*";
P_HTM[6058]="*ayaṃ tattha tassapāpiyasikāya.* **";
P_HTM[6059]="*Evaṃ vūpasantañce, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ kārako ukkoṭeti, ukkoṭanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ;**When a legal issue has been resolved like this, if any of the participants reopen it, they incur an offense entailing confession for the reopening.*";
P_HTM[6060]="*chandadāyako khīyati, khīyanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If anyone who gave their consent criticizes the resolution, they incur an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6061]="*9.8. Paṭiññātakaraṇa**9.8 Acting according to what has been admitted*";
P_HTM[6062]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ katihi samathehi sammati?* **";
P_HTM[6063]="*Āpattādhikaraṇaṃ tīhi samathehi sammati—**“There are three principles for settling a legal issue arising from an offense:*";
P_HTM[6064]="*sammukhāvinayena ca, paṭiññātakaraṇena ca, tiṇavatthārakena ca.**resolution face-to-face, acting according to what has been admitted, and covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6065]="*Siyā āpattādhikaraṇaṃ ekaṃ samathaṃ anāgamma—**Can it be that a legal issue arising from an accusation should be settled*";
P_HTM[6066]="*tiṇavatthārakaṃ, dvīhi samathehi sammeyya—**not by covering over as if with grass,*";
P_HTM[6067]="*sammukhāvinayena ca, paṭiññātakaraṇena cāti?**but by resolution face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted?*";
P_HTM[6068]="*Siyātissa vacanīyaṃ.**It can.*";
P_HTM[6069]="*Yathā kathaṃ viya?**How is that?*";
P_HTM[6070]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu lahukaṃ āpattiṃ āpanno hoti.**It may be that a monk has committed a light offense.*";
P_HTM[6071]="*Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā ekaṃ bhikkhuṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**That monk should approach a single monk, put his upper robe over one shoulder, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and say:*";
P_HTM[6072]="*‘ahaṃ, āvuso, itthannāmaṃ āpattiṃ āpanno;**‘I have committed such-and-such an offense.*";
P_HTM[6073]="*taṃ paṭidesemī’ti.**I confess it.’*";
P_HTM[6074]="*Tena vattabbo—**—*";
P_HTM[6075]="*‘passasī’ti?**‘Do you recognize the offense?’ —*";
P_HTM[6076]="*‘Āma passāmī’ti.**‘Yes, I recognize it.’ —*";
P_HTM[6077]="*‘Āyatiṃ saṃvareyyāsī’ti.**‘You should restrain yourself in the future.’*";
P_HTM[6078]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasantaṃ.**This is called the resolution of a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[6079]="*Kena vūpasantaṃ?* **";
P_HTM[6080]="*Sammukhāvinayena ca, paṭiññātakaraṇena ca.**It has been resolved face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted.*";
P_HTM[6081]="*Kiñca tattha sammukhāvinayasmiṃ?**Face-to-face with what?*";
P_HTM[6082]="*Dhammasammukhatā, vinayasammukhatā, puggalasammukhatā …pe…**Face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law, face-to-face with the persons concerned. This is the meaning of face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law: the Teaching, the Monastic Law, the Teacher’s instruction—that by which that legal issue is resolved.*";
P_HTM[6083]="*kā ca tattha puggalasammukhatā?**This is the meaning of face-to-face with the persons concerned:*";
P_HTM[6084]="*Yo ca deseti, yassa ca deseti, ubho sammukhībhūtā honti—**both the one who confesses and the one he confesses to are present.*";
P_HTM[6085]="*ayaṃ tattha puggalasammukhatā.* **";
P_HTM[6086]="*Kiñca tattha paṭiññātakaraṇasmiṃ?**This is the meaning of acting according to what has been admitted:*";
P_HTM[6087]="*Yā paṭiññātakaraṇassa kammassa kiriyā karaṇaṃ upagamanaṃ ajjhupagamanaṃ adhivāsanā appaṭikkosanā—**the doing of, the performing of, the participation in, the consent to, the agreement to, the non-objection to that legal procedure of acting according to what has been admitted.*";
P_HTM[6088]="*idaṃ tattha paṭiññātakaraṇasmiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6089]="*Evaṃ vūpasantañce, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ paṭiggāhako ukkoṭeti, ukkoṭanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**When a legal issue has been resolved like this, if the receiver of the confession reopens it, he incurs an offense entailing confession for the reopening.*";
P_HTM[6090]="*Evañcetaṃ labhetha, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ.**If this is what happens, all is well.*";
P_HTM[6091]="*No ce labhetha, tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā sambahule bhikkhū upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassu vacanīyā—**If not, that monk should approach several monks, put his upper robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[6092]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, itthannāmaṃ āpattiṃ āpanno;**‘Venerables, I have committed such-and-such an offense.*";
P_HTM[6093]="*taṃ paṭidesemī’ti.**I confess it.’*";
P_HTM[6094]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena te bhikkhū ñāpetabbā—**A competent and capable monk should then inform those monks:*";
P_HTM[6095]="*‘Suṇantu me āyasmantā.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask you to listen.*";
P_HTM[6096]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu āpattiṃ sarati, vivarati, uttāniṃ karoti deseti.**The monk so-and-so remembers an offense—he reveals it, makes it plain, and confesses it.*";
P_HTM[6097]="*Yadāyasmantānaṃ pattakallaṃ, ahaṃ itthannāmassa bhikkhuno āpattiṃ paṭiggaṇheyyan’ti.**If it seems appropriate to the venerables, I will receive the confession.’*";
P_HTM[6098]="*Tena vattabbo—**And he should say:*";
P_HTM[6099]="*‘passasī’ti?**‘Do you recognize the offense?’ —*";
P_HTM[6100]="*‘Āma passāmī’ti.**‘Yes, I recognize it.’ —*";
P_HTM[6101]="*‘Āyatiṃ saṃvareyyāsī’ti.**‘You should restrain yourself in the future.’*";
P_HTM[6102]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasantaṃ.**This is called the resolution of a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[6103]="*Kena vūpasantaṃ?* **";
P_HTM[6104]="*Sammukhāvinayena ca, paṭiññātakaraṇena ca.**It has been resolved face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted.*";
P_HTM[6105]="*Kiñca tattha sammukhāvinayasmiṃ?**Face-to-face with what?*";
P_HTM[6106]="*Dhammasammukhatā, vinayasammukhatā, puggalasammukhatā …pe…**Face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law, face-to-face with the persons concerned. This is the meaning of face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law: the Teaching, the Monastic Law, the Teacher’s instruction—that by which that legal issue is resolved.*";
P_HTM[6107]="*kā ca tattha puggalasammukhatā?**This is the meaning of face-to-face with the persons concerned:*";
P_HTM[6108]="*Yo ca deseti, yassa ca deseti, ubho sammukhībhūtā honti—**both the one who confesses and the one he confesses to are present.*";
P_HTM[6109]="*ayaṃ tattha puggalasammukhatā.* **";
P_HTM[6110]="*Kiñca tattha paṭiññātakaraṇasmiṃ?**This is the meaning of acting according to what has been admitted:*";
P_HTM[6111]="*Yā paṭiññātakaraṇassa kammassa kiriyā karaṇaṃ upagamanaṃ ajjhupagamanaṃ adhivāsanā appaṭikkosanā—**the doing of, the performing of, the participation in, the consent to, the agreement to, the non-objection to that legal procedure of acting according to what has been admitted.*";
P_HTM[6112]="*idaṃ tattha paṭiññātakaraṇasmiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6113]="*Evaṃ vūpasantañce, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ paṭiggāhako ukkoṭeti, ukkoṭanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**When a legal issue has been resolved like this, if the receiver of the confession reopens it, he incurs an offense entailing confession for the reopening.*";
P_HTM[6114]="*Evañcetaṃ labhetha, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ.**If this is what happens, all is well.*";
P_HTM[6115]="*No ce labhetha, tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**If not, that monk should approach the Sangha, put his upper robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[6116]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, itthannāmaṃ āpattiṃ āpanno;**‘Venerables, I have committed such-and-such an offense.*";
P_HTM[6117]="*taṃ paṭidesemī’ti.**I confess it.’*";
P_HTM[6118]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[6119]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[6120]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu āpattiṃ sarati, vivarati, uttāniṃ karoti, deseti.**The monk so-and-so remembers an offense—he reveals it, makes it plain, and confesses it.*";
P_HTM[6121]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, ahaṃ itthannāmassa bhikkhuno āpattiṃ paṭiggaṇheyyan’ti.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, I will receive the confession.’*";
P_HTM[6122]="*Tena vattabbo—**And he should say:*";
P_HTM[6123]="*‘passasī’ti?**‘Do you recognize the offense?’ —*";
P_HTM[6124]="*‘Āma passāmī’ti.**‘Yes, I recognize it.’ —*";
P_HTM[6125]="*‘Āyatiṃ saṃvareyyāsī’ti.**‘You should restrain yourself in the future.’*";
P_HTM[6126]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasantaṃ.**This is called the resolution of a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[6127]="*Kena vūpasantaṃ?* **";
P_HTM[6128]="*Sammukhāvinayena ca, paṭiññātakaraṇena ca.**It has been resolved face-to-face and by acting according to what has been admitted.*";
P_HTM[6129]="*Kiñca tattha sammukhāvinayasmiṃ?**Face-to-face with what?*";
P_HTM[6130]="*Saṅghasammukhatā, dhammasammukhatā, vinayasammukhatā, puggalasammukhatā …pe…**Face-to-face with the Sangha, face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law, face-to-face with the persons concerned. This is the meaning of face-to-face with the Sangha: the monks who should be present have arrived, consent has been brought for those who are eligible to give their consent, and no one present objects to the decision. This is the meaning of face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law: the Teaching, the Monastic Law, the Teacher’s instruction—that by which that legal issue is resolved. This is the meaning of face-to-face with the persons concerned: both the one who confesses and the one he confesses to are present. This is the meaning of acting according to what has been admitted: the doing of, the performing of, the participation in, the consent to, the agreement to, the non-objection to that legal procedure of acting according to what has been admitted.*";
P_HTM[6131]="*evaṃ vūpasantañce, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ paṭiggāhako ukkoṭeti, ukkoṭanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ;**When a legal issue has been resolved like this, if the receiver of the confession reopens it, he incurs an offense entailing confession for the reopening.*";
P_HTM[6132]="*chandadāyako khīyati, khīyanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If anyone who gave their consent criticizes the resolution, they incur an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6133]="*9.9. Tiṇavatthāraka**9.9 Covering over as if with grass*";
P_HTM[6134]="*Siyā āpattādhikaraṇaṃ ekaṃ samathaṃ anāgamma—**“Can it be that a legal issue arising from an offense should be settled*";
P_HTM[6135]="*paṭiññātakaraṇaṃ, dvīhi samathehi sammeyya—**not by acting according to what has been admitted,*";
P_HTM[6136]="*sammukhāvinayena ca, tiṇavatthārakena cāti?**but by resolution face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass?*";
P_HTM[6137]="*Siyātissa vacanīyaṃ.**It can.*";
P_HTM[6138]="*Yathā kathaṃ viya?**How is that?*";
P_HTM[6139]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ viharataṃ bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ hoti bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**It may be that monks who are arguing and disputing do and say many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[6140]="*Tatra ce bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ hoti—**If they consider this and think,*";
P_HTM[6141]="*‘amhākaṃ kho bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ viharataṃ bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6142]="*Sace mayaṃ imāhi āpattīhi aññamaññaṃ kāressāma, siyāpi taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ kakkhaḷattāya vāḷattāya bhedāya saṃvatteyyā’ti.**‘If we deal with one another for these offenses, this legal issue might lead to harshness, nastiness, and schism,’*";
P_HTM[6143]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, evarūpaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ tiṇavatthārakena vūpasametuṃ.**then I allow you to resolve this legal issue by covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6144]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, vūpasametabbaṃ.**And it should be resolved like this.*";
P_HTM[6145]="*Sabbeheva ekajjhaṃ sannipatitabbaṃ, sannipatitvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**Everyone should gather in one place. A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[6146]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[6147]="*Amhākaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ viharataṃ bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**While we were arguing and disputing, we did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[6148]="*Sace mayaṃ imāhi āpattīhi aññamaññaṃ kāressāma, siyāpi taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ kakkhaḷattāya vāḷattāya bhedāya saṃvatteyya.**If we deal with one another for these offenses, this legal issue might lead to harshness, nastiness, and schism.*";
P_HTM[6149]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ tiṇavatthārakena vūpasameyya, ṭhapetvā thullavajjaṃ, ṭhapetvā gihippaṭisaṃyuttanti.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should resolve this legal issue by covering over as if with grass, except for heavy offenses and offenses connected with householders.’*";
P_HTM[6150]="*Ekatopakkhikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena sako pakkho ñāpetabbo—**The monks belonging to one side should be informed by a competent and capable monk belonging to their own side:*";
P_HTM[6151]="*Suṇantu me āyasmantā.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask you to listen.*";
P_HTM[6152]="*Amhākaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ viharataṃ bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**While we were arguing and disputing, we did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[6153]="*Sace mayaṃ imāhi āpattīhi aññamaññaṃ kāressāma, siyāpi taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ kakkhaḷattāya vāḷattāya bhedāya saṃvatteyya.**If we deal with one another for these offenses, this legal issue might lead to harshness, nastiness, and schism.*";
P_HTM[6154]="*Yadāyasmantānaṃ pattakallaṃ, ahaṃ yā ceva āyasmantānaṃ āpatti, yā ca attano āpatti, āyasmantānañceva atthāya, attano ca atthāya, saṅghamajjhe tiṇavatthārakena deseyyaṃ, ṭhapetvā thullavajjaṃ, ṭhapetvā gihippaṭisaṃyuttan’ti.**If it seems appropriate to the venerables, then for your benefit and for my own, I will confess in the midst of the Sangha both your and my own offenses by covering over as if with grass, except for heavy offenses and offenses connected with householders.’*";
P_HTM[6155]="*Athāparesaṃ ekatopakkhikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena sako pakkho ñāpetabbo—**The monks belonging to the other side should be informed by a competent and capable monk belonging to their own side:*";
P_HTM[6156]="*‘Suṇantu me āyasmantā.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask you to listen.*";
P_HTM[6157]="*Amhākaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ viharataṃ bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**While we were arguing and disputing, we did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[6158]="*Sace mayaṃ imāhi āpattīhi aññamaññaṃ kāressāma, siyāpi taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ kakkhaḷattāya vāḷattāya bhedāya saṃvatteyya.**If we deal with one another for these offenses, this legal issue might lead to harshness, nastiness, and schism.*";
P_HTM[6159]="*Yadāyasmantānaṃ pattakallaṃ, ahaṃ yā ceva āyasmantānaṃ āpatti, yā ca attano āpatti, āyasmantānañceva atthāya, attano ca atthāya, saṅghamajjhe tiṇavatthārakena deseyyaṃ, ṭhapetvā thullavajjaṃ, ṭhapetvā gihippaṭisaṃyuttan’ti.**If it seems appropriate to the venerables, then for your benefit and for my own, I will confess in the midst of the Sangha both your and my own offenses by covering over as if with grass, except for heavy offenses and offenses connected with householders.’*";
P_HTM[6160]="*Athāparesaṃ ekatopakkhikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk belonging to one side should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[6161]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[6162]="*Amhākaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ viharataṃ bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**While we were arguing and disputing, we did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[6163]="*Sace mayaṃ imāhi āpattīhi aññamaññaṃ kāressāma, siyāpi taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ kakkhaḷattāya vāḷattāya bhedāya saṃvatteyya.**If we deal with one another for these offenses, this legal issue might lead to harshness, nastiness, and schism.*";
P_HTM[6164]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, ahaṃ yā ceva imesaṃ āyasmantānaṃ āpatti, yā ca attano āpatti, imesañceva āyasmantānaṃ atthāya, attano ca atthāya, saṅghamajjhe tiṇavatthārakena deseyyaṃ, ṭhapetvā thullavajjaṃ, ṭhapetvā gihippaṭisaṃyuttaṃ.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, for the benefit of these venerables and myself, I will confess in the midst of the Sangha both their and my own offenses by covering over as if with grass, except for heavy offenses and offenses connected with householders.*";
P_HTM[6165]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[6166]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[6167]="*Amhākaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ viharataṃ bahuṃ assāmaṇakaṃ ajjhāciṇṇaṃ bhāsitaparikkantaṃ.**While we were arguing and disputing, we did and said many things unworthy of a monastic.*";
P_HTM[6168]="*Sace mayaṃ imāhi āpattīhi aññamaññaṃ kāressāma, siyāpi taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ kakkhaḷattāya vāḷattāya bhedāya saṃvatteyya.**If we deal with one another for these offenses, this legal issue might lead to harshness, nastiness, and schism.*";
P_HTM[6169]="*Ahaṃ yā ceva imesaṃ āyasmantānaṃ āpatti, yā ca attano āpatti, imesañceva āyasmantānaṃ atthāya, attano ca atthāya, saṅghamajjhe tiṇavatthārakena desemi, ṭhapetvā thullavajjaṃ, ṭhapetvā gihippaṭisaṃyuttaṃ.**For the benefit of these venerables and myself, I confess both their and my own offenses in the midst of the Sangha by covering over as if with grass, except for heavy offenses and offenses connected with householders.*";
P_HTM[6170]="*Yassāyasmato khamati amhākaṃ imāsaṃ āpattīnaṃ saṅghamajjhe tiṇavatthārakena desanā, ṭhapetvā thullavajjaṃ, ṭhapetvā gihippaṭisaṃyuttaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of the confession in the midst of the Sangha of both their and my own offenses by covering over as if with grass, except for heavy offenses and offenses connected with householders, should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[6171]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[6172]="*Desitā amhākaṃ imā āpattiyo saṅghamajjhe tiṇavatthārakena, ṭhapetvā thullavajjaṃ, ṭhapetvā gihippaṭisaṃyuttaṃ.**We have confessed these offenses in the midst of the Sangha by covering over as if with grass, except for heavy offenses and offenses connected with householders.*";
P_HTM[6173]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[6174]="*Athāparesaṃ …pe…**A competent and capable monk belonging to the other side should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[6175]="*evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[6176]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasantaṃ.**This is called the resolution of a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[6177]="*Kena vūpasantaṃ?* **";
P_HTM[6178]="*Sammukhāvinayena ca, tiṇavatthārakena ca.**It has been resolved face-to-face and by covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6179]="*Kiñca tattha sammukhāvinayasmiṃ?**Face-to-face with what?*";
P_HTM[6180]="*Saṅghasammukhatā, dhammasammukhatā, vinayasammukhatā, puggalasammukhatā.**Face-to-face with the Sangha, face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law, face-to-face with the persons concerned.*";
P_HTM[6181]="*Kā ca tattha saṅghasammukhatā?**This is the meaning of face-to-face with the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[6182]="*Yāvatikā bhikkhū kammappattā, te āgatā honti, chandārahānaṃ chando āhaṭo hoti, sammukhībhūtā na paṭikkosanti—**the monks who should be present have arrived, consent has been brought for those who are eligible to give their consent, and no one present objects to the decision.*";
P_HTM[6183]="*ayaṃ tattha saṅghasammukhatā.* **";
P_HTM[6184]="*Kā ca tattha dhammasammukhatā, vinayasammukhatā?**This is the meaning of face-to-face with the Teaching, face-to-face with the Monastic Law:*";
P_HTM[6185]="*Yena dhammena yena vinayena yena satthusāsanena taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasammati—**the Teaching, the Monastic Law, the Teacher’s instruction—that by which that legal issue is resolved.*";
P_HTM[6186]="*ayaṃ tattha dhammasammukhatā, vinayasammukhatā.* **";
P_HTM[6187]="*Kā ca tattha puggalasammukhatā?**This is the meaning of face-to-face with the persons concerned:*";
P_HTM[6188]="*Yo ca deseti, yassa ca deseti, ubho sammukhībhūtā honti—**both the one who confesses and the one he confesses to are present.*";
P_HTM[6189]="*ayaṃ tattha puggalasammukhatā.* **";
P_HTM[6190]="*Kiñca tattha tiṇavatthārakasmiṃ?**This is the meaning of covering over as if with grass:*";
P_HTM[6191]="*Yā tiṇavatthārakassa kammassa kiriyā karaṇaṃ upagamanaṃ ajjhupagamanaṃ adhivāsanā appaṭikkosanā—**the doing of, the performing of, the participation in, the consent to, the agreement to, the non-objection to that legal procedure of covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[6192]="*idaṃ tattha tiṇavatthārakasmiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6193]="*Evaṃ vūpasantañce, bhikkhave, adhikaraṇaṃ paṭiggāhako ukkoṭeti, ukkoṭanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ;**When a legal issue has been resolved like this, if the receiver of the confession reopens it, he incurs an offense entailing confession for the reopening.*";
P_HTM[6194]="*chandadāyako khīyati, khīyanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If anyone who gave their consent criticizes the resolution, they incur an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6195]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ katihi samathehi sammati?* **";
P_HTM[6196]="*Kiccādhikaraṇaṃ ekena samathena sammati—**There is one way of settling a legal issue arising from business:*";
P_HTM[6197]="*sammukhāvinayenā”ti.**resolution face-to-face.”*";
P_HTM[6198]="*Samathakkhandhako niṭṭhito catuttho.**The fourth chapter on the settling of legal issues is finished.*";
P_HTM[6199]="*5. Khuddakavatthukkhandhaka **5.  The chapter with short topics *";
P_HTM[6200]="*1. Khuddakavatthu**The short topics*";
P_HTM[6201]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[6202]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū nahāyamānā rukkhe kāyaṃ ugghaṃsenti, ūrumpi bāhumpi urampi piṭṭhimpi.**At that time the monks from the group of six rubbed their bodies—thighs, arms, chest, and back—against trees while bathing.*";
P_HTM[6203]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6204]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā nahāyamānā rukkhe kāyaṃ ugghaṃsessanti, ūrumpi bāhumpi urampi piṭṭhimpi, seyyathāpi mallamuṭṭhikā gāmamoddavā”ti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics act like this? They are just like boxers and city slickers who beautify their bodies.”*";
P_HTM[6205]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people*";
P_HTM[6206]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**and they told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6207]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[6208]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū nahāyamānā rukkhe kāyaṃ ugghaṃsenti, ūrumpi bāhumpi urampi piṭṭhimpī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the monks from the group of six are acting like this?”*";
P_HTM[6209]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[6210]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—**The Buddha criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6211]="*“ananucchavikaṃ, bhikkhave, tesaṃ moghapurisānaṃ ananulomikaṃ appatirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ akaraṇīyaṃ.**“It’s not suitable for those foolish men, it’s not proper, it’s not worthy of a monastic, it’s not allowable, it’s not to be done.*";
P_HTM[6212]="*Kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā nahāyamānā rukkhe kāyaṃ ugghaṃsessanti, ūrumpi bāhumpi urampi piṭṭhimpi?**How can they act like this?*";
P_HTM[6213]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[6214]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[6215]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[6216]="*“na, bhikkhave, nahāyamānena bhikkhunā rukkhe kāyo ugghaṃsetabbo.**“You should not rub your body against a tree while bathing.*";
P_HTM[6217]="*Yo ugghaṃseyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6218]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū nahāyamānā thambhe kāyaṃ ugghaṃsenti, ūrumpi bāhumpi urampi piṭṭhimpi.**At that time the monks from the group of six rubbed their bodies—thighs, arms, chest, and back—against posts while bathing.*";
P_HTM[6219]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6220]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā nahāyamānā thambhe kāyaṃ ugghaṃsessanti, ūrumpi bāhumpi urampi piṭṭhimpi, seyyathāpi mallamuṭṭhikā gāmamoddavā”ti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics act like this? They are just like boxers and city slickers who beautify their bodies.”*";
P_HTM[6221]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people*";
P_HTM[6222]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**and they told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[6223]="*“saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[6224]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[6225]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[6226]="*“na, bhikkhave, nahāyamānena bhikkhunā thambhe kāyo ugghaṃsetabbo.**“You should not rub your body against a post while bathing.*";
P_HTM[6227]="*Yo ugghaṃseyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6228]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū nahāyamānā kuṭṭe kāyaṃ ugghaṃsenti, ūrumpi bāhumpi urampi piṭṭhimpi.**At that time the monks from the group of six rubbed their bodies—thighs, arms, chest, and back—against walls while bathing.*";
P_HTM[6229]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6230]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā nahāyamānā kuṭṭe kāyaṃ ugghaṃsessanti, ūrumpi bāhumpi urampi piṭṭhimpi, seyyathāpi mallamuṭṭhikā gāmamoddavā”ti …pe…**“How can the Sakyan monastics act like this? They are just like boxers and city slickers who beautify their bodies.”*";
P_HTM[6231]="*“na, bhikkhave, nahāyamānena bhikkhunā kuṭṭe kāyo ugghaṃsetabbo.**“You should not rub your body against a wall while bathing.*";
P_HTM[6232]="*Yo ugghaṃseyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6233]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū aṭṭāne nahāyanti.**At that time the monks from the group of six rubbed their bodies—thighs, arms, chest, and back—against a rubbing board while bathing.*";
P_HTM[6234]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti …pe…**People complained and criticized them, “How can the Sakyan monastics act like this?*";
P_HTM[6235]="*seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[6236]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6237]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…* **";
P_HTM[6238]="*“saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…* **";
P_HTM[6239]="*vigarahitvā …pe…* **";
P_HTM[6240]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—* **";
P_HTM[6241]="*“na, bhikkhave, aṭṭāne nahāyitabbaṃ.**“You should not rub your body against a rubbing board while bathing.*";
P_HTM[6242]="*Yo nahāyeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6243]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū gandhabbahatthakena nahāyanti.**At that time the monks from the group of six bathed with a wooden rubbing-hand.*";
P_HTM[6244]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti …pe…**People complained and criticized them, “How can the Sakyan monastics act like this?*";
P_HTM[6245]="*seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[6246]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people*";
P_HTM[6247]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**and they told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[6248]="*“na, bhikkhave, gandhabbahatthakena nahāyitabbaṃ.**“You should not bathe with a wooden rubbing-hand.*";
P_HTM[6249]="*Yo nahāyeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6250]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kuruvindakasuttiyā nahāyanti.**At that time the monks from the group of six bathed with a string of cinnabar beads.*";
P_HTM[6251]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti …pe…**People complained and criticized them, “How can the Sakyan monastics act like this?*";
P_HTM[6252]="*seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhoginoti.**They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[6253]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6254]="*“Na, bhikkhave, kuruvindakasuttiyā nahāyitabbaṃ.**“You should not bathe with a string of cinnabar beads.*";
P_HTM[6255]="*Yo nahāyeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6256]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū viggayha parikammaṃ kārāpenti.**At that time the monks from the group of six massaged one another.*";
P_HTM[6257]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti …pe…**People complained and criticized them, “How can the Sakyan monastics act like this?*";
P_HTM[6258]="*seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[6259]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6260]="*“Na, bhikkhave, viggayha parikammaṃ kārāpetabbaṃ.**“You should not massage one another.*";
P_HTM[6261]="*Yo kārāpeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6262]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū mallakena nahāyanti.**At that time the monks from the group of six bathed with an ornamented scrubber.*";
P_HTM[6263]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti …pe…**People complained and criticized them, “How can the Sakyan monastics act like this?*";
P_HTM[6264]="*seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!” …*";
P_HTM[6265]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6266]="*“Na, bhikkhave, mallakena nahāyitabbaṃ.**“You should not bathe with an ornamented scrubber.*";
P_HTM[6267]="*Yo nahāyeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6268]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa bhikkhuno kacchurogābādho hoti.**Soon afterwards a certain monk had an itchy skin disease.*";
P_HTM[6269]="*Na tassa vinā mallakena phāsu hoti.**He was not comfortable without a scrubber.*";
P_HTM[6270]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6271]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānassa akatamallakan”ti.**“I allow a plain scrubber for those who are sick.”*";
P_HTM[6272]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu jarādubbalo nahāyamāno na sakkoti attano kāyaṃ ugghaṃsetuṃ.**At that time a monk who was weak from old age was unable to rub his own body while bathing.*";
P_HTM[6273]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6274]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ukkāsikan”ti.**“I allow gloves of cloth.”*";
P_HTM[6275]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū piṭṭhiparikammaṃ kātuṃ kukkuccāyanti.**Being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not give back massages.*";
P_HTM[6276]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6277]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, puthupāṇikan”ti.**“I allow an ordinary massage by hand.”*";
P_HTM[6278]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū vallikaṃ dhārenti …pe…**At that time the monks from the group of six wore earrings,*";
P_HTM[6279]="*pāmaṅgaṃ dhārenti …pe…**ornamental hanging strings,*";
P_HTM[6280]="*kaṇṭhasuttakaṃ dhārenti …pe…**necklaces,*";
P_HTM[6281]="*kaṭisuttakaṃ dhārenti …pe…**ornamental girdles,*";
P_HTM[6282]="*ovaṭṭikaṃ dhārenti …pe…**bangles,*";
P_HTM[6283]="*kāyuraṃ dhārenti …pe…**armlets,*";
P_HTM[6284]="*hatthābharaṇaṃ dhārenti …pe…**bracelets,*";
P_HTM[6285]="*aṅgulimuddikaṃ dhārenti.**and rings.*";
P_HTM[6286]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti …pe…**People complained and criticized them …*";
P_HTM[6287]="*seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“… They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[6288]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people.*";
P_HTM[6289]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6290]="*“Saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū vallikaṃ dhārenti …pe…**“Is it true, monks, that the monks from the group of six are wearing these things?”*";
P_HTM[6291]="*pāmaṅgaṃ dhārenti, kaṇṭhasuttakaṃ dhārenti, kaṭisuttakaṃ dhārenti, ovaṭṭikaṃ dhārenti, kāyuraṃ dhārenti, hatthābharaṇaṃ dhārenti, aṅgulimuddikaṃ dhārentī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6292]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[6293]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[6294]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[6295]="*“na, bhikkhave, vallikā dhāretabbā …pe…**“You should not wear earrings,*";
P_HTM[6296]="*na pāmaṅgo dhāretabbo …**an ornamental hanging string,*";
P_HTM[6297]="*na kaṇṭhasuttakaṃ dhāretabbaṃ …**a necklace,*";
P_HTM[6298]="*na kaṭisuttakaṃ dhāretabbaṃ …**an ornamental girdle,*";
P_HTM[6299]="*na ovaṭṭikaṃ dhāretabbaṃ …**a bangle,*";
P_HTM[6300]="*na kāyuraṃ dhāretabbaṃ …**an armlet,*";
P_HTM[6301]="*na hatthābharaṇaṃ dhāretabbaṃ …**a bracelet,*";
P_HTM[6302]="*na aṅgulimuddikā dhāretabbā.**or a ring.*";
P_HTM[6303]="*Yo dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6304]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū dīghe kese dhārenti.**At that time the monks from the group of six grew their hair long.*";
P_HTM[6305]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6306]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[6307]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6308]="*“Na, bhikkhave, dīghā kesā dhāretabbā.**“You should not grow your hair long.*";
P_HTM[6309]="*Yo dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6310]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, dumāsikaṃ vā duvaṅgulaṃ vā”ti.**I allow you to grow it to a length of 3.5 centimeters or for two months at the most.”*";
P_HTM[6311]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kocchena kese osaṇṭhenti …pe…**At that time the monks from the group of six brushed their hair,*";
P_HTM[6312]="*phaṇakena kese osaṇṭhenti, hatthaphaṇakena kese osaṇṭhenti, sitthatelakena kese osaṇṭhenti, udakatelakena kese osaṇṭhenti.**combed their hair, combed their hair with their hands, smoothed their hair with beeswax, and smoothed their hair with water and oil.*";
P_HTM[6313]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6314]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[6315]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6316]="*“Na, bhikkhave, kocchena kesā osaṇṭhetabbā …pe…**“You should not brush your hair, comb your hair, comb your hair with your hands,*";
P_HTM[6317]="*na sitthatelakena kesā osaṇṭhetabbā …**smooth your hair with beeswax,*";
P_HTM[6318]="*na udakatelakena kesā osaṇṭhetabbā.**or smooth your hair with water and oil.*";
P_HTM[6319]="*Yo osaṇṭheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6320]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū ādāsepi udakapattepi mukhanimittaṃ olokenti.**At that time the monks from the group of six looked at their faces in mirrors or in bowls of water.*";
P_HTM[6321]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6322]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[6323]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6324]="*“Na, bhikkhave, ādāse vā udakapatte vā mukhanimittaṃ oloketabbaṃ.**“You should not look at your face in a mirror or in a bowl of water.*";
P_HTM[6325]="*Yo olokeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6326]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa bhikkhuno mukhe vaṇo hoti.**Soon afterwards a certain monk had a sore on his face.*";
P_HTM[6327]="*So bhikkhū pucchi—**He asked the monks,*";
P_HTM[6328]="*“kīdiso me, āvuso, vaṇo”ti?**“What kind of sore is it?”*";
P_HTM[6329]="*Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—**They replied,*";
P_HTM[6330]="*“ediso te, āvuso vaṇo”ti.**“It’s such-and-such a kind of sore.”*";
P_HTM[6331]="*So na saddahati.**He did not trust them.*";
P_HTM[6332]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6333]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ābādhappaccayā ādāse vā udakapatte vā mukhanimittaṃ oloketun”ti.**“I allow you to look at your face in a mirror or in a bowl of water if you have a disease.”*";
P_HTM[6334]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū mukhaṃ ālimpanti …pe…**At that time the monks from the group of six used facial ointments,*";
P_HTM[6335]="*mukhaṃ ummaddenti, mukhaṃ cuṇṇenti, manosilikāya mukhaṃ lañchenti, aṅgarāgaṃ karonti, mukharāgaṃ karonti, aṅgarāgamukharāgaṃ karonti.**applied facial creams, powdered the face, applied rouge to the face, wore cosmetics on the body, wore cosmetics on the face, and wore cosmetics on the body and the face.*";
P_HTM[6336]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6337]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[6338]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6339]="*“Na, bhikkhave, mukhaṃ ālimpitabbaṃ …pe…**“You should not use facial ointments,*";
P_HTM[6340]="*na mukhaṃ ummadditabbaṃ, na mukhaṃ cuṇṇetabbaṃ, na manosilikāya mukhaṃ lañchetabbaṃ, na aṅgarāgo kātabbo, na mukharāgo kātabbo, na aṅgarāgamukharāgo kātabbo.**apply creams, powder your face, apply rouge to your face, wear cosmetics on the body, wear cosmetics on the face, or wear cosmetics on the body and the face.*";
P_HTM[6341]="*Yo kareyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6342]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa bhikkhuno cakkhurogābādho hoti.**Soon afterwards a certain monk had an eye disease.*";
P_HTM[6343]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6344]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ābādhappaccayā mukhaṃ ālimpitun”ti.**“I allow facial ointments for those who are sick.”*";
P_HTM[6345]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājagahe giraggasamajjo hoti.**On one occasion in Rājagaha there was a hilltop fair,*";
P_HTM[6346]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū giraggasamajjaṃ dassanāya agamaṃsu.**and the monks from the group of six went to see it.*";
P_HTM[6347]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6348]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā naccampi gītampi vāditampi dassanāya gacchissanti, seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics go to see dancing, singing, and the playing of music? They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[6349]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6350]="*“Na, bhikkhave, naccaṃ vā gītaṃ vā vāditaṃ vā dassanāya gantabbaṃ.**“You should not go to see dancing, singing, and the playing of music.*";
P_HTM[6351]="*Yo gaccheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6352]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū āyatakena gītassarena dhammaṃ gāyanti.**At that time the monks from the group of six recited the Teaching by singing in a drawn-out fashion.*";
P_HTM[6353]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6354]="*“yatheva mayaṃ gāyāma, evamevime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā āyatakena gītassarena dhammaṃ gāyantī”ti.**“These Sakyan monastics sing just like we do.”*";
P_HTM[6355]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[6356]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6357]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū āyatakena gītassarena dhammaṃ gāyissantī”ti.**“How can the monks from the group of six sing like this?”*";
P_HTM[6358]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6359]="*“Saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave …pe…**“Is it true, monks, that the monks from the group of six are singing like this?”*";
P_HTM[6360]="*“saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[6361]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[6362]="*“pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā āyatakena gītassarena dhammaṃ gāyantassa.**“There are these five dangers in reciting the Teaching by singing in a drawn-out fashion:*";
P_HTM[6363]="*Attanāpi tasmiṃ sare sārajjati, parepi tasmiṃ sare sārajjanti, gahapatikāpi ujjhāyanti, sarakuttimpi nikāmayamānassa samādhissa bhaṅgo hoti, pacchimā janatā diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjati—**one delights in the sound; others delight in the sound; householders criticize it; for one who takes pleasure in the melody, the concentration is disrupted; later generations follow one’s example.*";
P_HTM[6364]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā āyatakena gītassarena dhammaṃ gāyantassa.* **";
P_HTM[6365]="*Na, bhikkhave, āyatakena gītassarena dhammo gāyitabbo.**You should not recite the Teaching by singing in a drawn-out fashion.*";
P_HTM[6366]="*Yo gāyeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6367]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū sarabhaññe kukkuccāyanti.**Being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not chant.*";
P_HTM[6368]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6369]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, sarabhaññan”ti.**“I allow chanting.”*";
P_HTM[6370]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bāhiralomiṃ uṇṇiṃ dhārenti.**At that time the monks from the group of six wore fleecy woolen robes with the fleece on the outside.*";
P_HTM[6371]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6372]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[6373]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6374]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bāhiyalomi uṇṇi dhāretabbā.**“You should not wear a fleecy woolen robe with the fleece on the outside.*";
P_HTM[6375]="*Yo dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6376]="*Tena kho pana samayena rañño māgadhassa seniyassa bimbisārassa ārāme ambā phalino honti.**On one occasion when the mango trees in King Bimbisāra’s park were bearing fruit,*";
P_HTM[6377]="*Raññā māgadhena seniyena bimbisārena anuññātaṃ hoti—**the King allowed the monks*";
P_HTM[6378]="*“yathāsukhaṃ ayyā ambaṃ paribhuñjantū”ti.**to eat as many mangoes as they wished.*";
P_HTM[6379]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū taruṇaññeva ambaṃ pātāpetvā paribhuñjiṃsu.**The monks from the group of six plucked and ate them all, even the young ones.*";
P_HTM[6380]="*Rañño ca māgadhassa seniyassa bimbisārassa ambena attho hoti.**Just then the King needed mangoes.*";
P_HTM[6381]="*Atha kho rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro manusse āṇāpesi—**He told his people,*";
P_HTM[6382]="*“gacchatha, bhaṇe, ārāmaṃ gantvā ambaṃ āharathā”ti.**“Go to the park and bring back mangoes.”*";
P_HTM[6383]="*“Evaṃ, devā”ti kho te manussā rañño māgadhassa seniyassa bimbisārassa paṭissutvā ārāmaṃ gantvā ārāmapālaṃ etadavocuṃ—**Saying, “Yes, Sir,” they went to the park and said to the park keeper,*";
P_HTM[6384]="*“devassa, bhaṇe, ambena attho, ambaṃ dethā”ti.**“The King needs mangoes. Please get some.”*";
P_HTM[6385]="*“Natthāyyā, ambaṃ.**“There aren’t any.*";
P_HTM[6386]="*Taruṇaññeva ambaṃ pātāpetvā bhikkhū paribhuñjiṃsū”ti.**The monks plucked and ate them all, including the young ones.”*";
P_HTM[6387]="*Atha kho te manussā rañño māgadhassa seniyassa bimbisārassa etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They reported to the King what had happened. He said,*";
P_HTM[6388]="*“Suparibhuttaṃ, bhaṇe, ayyehi ambaṃ, api ca bhagavatā mattā vaṇṇitā”ti.**“It’s good that the venerables have eaten the mangoes. Still, the Buddha has praised moderation.”*";
P_HTM[6389]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6390]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā na mattaṃ jānitvā rañño ambaṃ paribhuñjissantī”ti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics eat the King’s mangoes without moderation?”*";
P_HTM[6391]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people*";
P_HTM[6392]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**and they told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6393]="*“Na, bhikkhave, ambaṃ paribhuñjitabbaṃ.**“You should not eat mangoes.*";
P_HTM[6394]="*Yo paribhuñjeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6395]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa pūgassa saṅghabhattaṃ hoti.**Soon afterwards a certain association was offering a meal to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[6396]="*Sūpe ambapesikāyo pakkhittā honti.**They had prepared mango curry.*";
P_HTM[6397]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nappaṭiggaṇhanti …pe…**Being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not accept it.*";
P_HTM[6398]="*“paṭiggaṇhatha, bhikkhave, paribhuñjatha.**“Accept and eat.*";
P_HTM[6399]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ambapesikan”ti.**I allow pieces of mango.”*";
P_HTM[6400]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa pūgassa saṅghabhattaṃ hoti.**Soon afterwards a certain association was offering a meal to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[6401]="*Te na pariyāpuṇiṃsu ambapesikaṃ kātuṃ, bhattagge sakaleheva ambehi denti.**They were unable to make mango pieces and so they gave whole mangoes in the dining hall.*";
P_HTM[6402]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nappaṭiggaṇhanti.**Being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not accept them.*";
P_HTM[6403]="*“Paṭiggaṇhatha, bhikkhave, paribhuñjatha.**“Accept and eat.*";
P_HTM[6404]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pañcahi samaṇakappehi phalaṃ paribhuñjituṃ—**I allow you to eat fruit that is allowable for monastics for any of five reasons:*";
P_HTM[6405]="*aggiparicitaṃ, satthaparicitaṃ, nakhaparicitaṃ, abījaṃ, nibbattabījaññeva pañcamaṃ.**it has been damaged by fire, it has been damaged by a knife, it has been damaged by a nail, it’s seedless, the seeds have been removed.”*";
P_HTM[6406]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, imehi pañcahi samaṇakappehi phalaṃ paribhuñjitun”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6407]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu ahinā daṭṭho kālaṅkato hoti.**On one occasion a monk had been bitten by a snake and died.*";
P_HTM[6408]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6409]="*“Na hi nūna so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu imāni cattāri ahirājakulāni mettena cittena phari.**“That monk had not radiated good will to the four royal snake clans.*";
P_HTM[6410]="*Sace hi so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu imāni cattāri ahirājakulāni mettena cittena phareyya, na hi so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ahinā daṭṭho kālaṃ kareyya.**Had he done so, he would not have died.*";
P_HTM[6411]="*Katamāni cattāri ahirājakulāni?**What are the four clans?*";
P_HTM[6412]="*Virūpakkhaṃ ahirājakulaṃ, erāpathaṃ ahirājakulaṃ, chabyāputtaṃ ahirājakulaṃ, kaṇhāgotamaṃ ahirājakulaṃ.**The Virūpakkhas, the Erāpathas, the Chabyāputtas, and the Kaṇhāgotamas.*";
P_HTM[6413]="*Na hi nūna so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu imāni cattāri ahirājakulāni mettena cittena phari.* **";
P_HTM[6414]="*Sace hi so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu imāni cattāri ahirājakulāni mettena cittena phareyya, na hi so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ahinā daṭṭho kālaṃ kareyya.* **";
P_HTM[6415]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, imāni cattāri ahirājakulāni mettena cittena pharituṃ, attaguttiyā attarakkhāya attaparittaṃ kātuṃ.**To protect yourselves, monks, you should spread good will to these four royal snake clans.*";
P_HTM[6416]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, kātabbaṃ—**And it should be done like this:*";
P_HTM[6417]="*‘Virūpakkhehi me mettaṃ,**I have good will toward the Virūpakkhas,*";
P_HTM[6418]="*Mettaṃ erāpathehi me;**Toward the Erāpathas I have good will;*";
P_HTM[6419]="*Chabyāputtehi me mettaṃ,**I have good will toward the Chabyāputtas,*";
P_HTM[6420]="*Mettaṃ kaṇhāgotamakehi ca.**And toward the Kaṇhāgotamas.*";
P_HTM[6421]="*Apādakehi me mettaṃ,**I have good will toward the legless,*";
P_HTM[6422]="*mettaṃ dvipādakehi me;**Toward the two-legged I have good will;*";
P_HTM[6423]="*Catuppadehi me mettaṃ,**I have good will toward the four-legged,*";
P_HTM[6424]="*mettaṃ bahuppadehi me.**And toward the many-legged.*";
P_HTM[6425]="*Mā maṃ apādako hiṃsi,**May the legless not hurt me,*";
P_HTM[6426]="*mā maṃ hiṃsi dvipādako;**May the two-legged not hurt me.*";
P_HTM[6427]="*Mā maṃ catuppado hiṃsi,**May the four-legged not hurt me,*";
P_HTM[6428]="*mā maṃ hiṃsi bahuppado.**May the many-legged not hurt me.*";
P_HTM[6429]="*Sabbe sattā sabbe pāṇā,**All beings, all creatures,*";
P_HTM[6430]="*sabbe bhūtā ca kevalā;**All living beings everywhere,*";
P_HTM[6431]="*Sabbe bhadrāni passantu,**May they all have good fortune,*";
P_HTM[6432]="*mā kiñci pāpamāgamā.**May none meet with anything bad.*";
P_HTM[6433]="*Appamāṇo buddho,**The Buddha is unlimited,*";
P_HTM[6434]="*Appamāṇo dhammo;**The Teaching is unlimited,*";
P_HTM[6435]="*Appamāṇo saṅgho,**The Sangha is unlimited.*";
P_HTM[6436]="*Pamāṇavantāni sarīsapāni.**But creeping animals are limited:*";
P_HTM[6437]="*Ahi vicchikā satapadī,**Snakes, scorpions, centipedes,*";
P_HTM[6438]="*Uṇṇanābhi sarabū mūsikā;**Spiders, lizards, and mice.*";
P_HTM[6439]="*Katā me rakkhā kataṃ me parittaṃ,**I’m now protected and guarded;*";
P_HTM[6440]="*Paṭikkamantu bhūtāni;**May the creatures turn back.*";
P_HTM[6441]="*Sohaṃ namo bhagavato,**I pay homage to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[6442]="*Namo sattannaṃ sammāsambuddhānan’”ti.**And to the seven fully awakened Buddhas.”*";
P_HTM[6443]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu anabhiratiyā pīḷito attano aṅgajātaṃ chindi.**On one occasion a monk who was plagued by lust cut off his own penis.*";
P_HTM[6444]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha. He said,*";
P_HTM[6445]="*“Aññamhi so, bhikkhave, moghapuriso chetabbamhi, aññaṃ chindi.**“This fool has cut off one thing, when he should have cut off something else.*";
P_HTM[6446]="*Na, bhikkhave, attano aṅgajātaṃ chetabbaṃ.**You should not cut off your own penis.*";
P_HTM[6447]="*Yo chindeyya, āpatti thullaccayassā”ti.**If you do, you commit a serious offense.”*";
P_HTM[6448]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājagahakassa seṭṭhissa mahagghassa candanassa candanagaṇṭhi uppannā hoti.**On one occasion a wealthy merchant of Rājagaha had obtained a very valuable block of sandalwood.*";
P_HTM[6449]="*Atha kho rājagahakassa seṭṭhissa etadahosi—**He thought,*";
P_HTM[6450]="*“yannūnāhaṃ imāya candanagaṇṭhiyā pattaṃ lekhāpeyyaṃ.**“Let me have a bowl carved from this block of sandal.*";
P_HTM[6451]="*Lekhañca me paribhogaṃ bhavissati, pattañca dānaṃ dassāmī”ti.**I’ll use the chips myself, but give the bowl away as a gift.”*";
P_HTM[6452]="*Atha kho rājagahako seṭṭhi tāya candanagaṇṭhiyā pattaṃ lekhāpetvā sikkāya uḍḍitvā veḷagge ālaggetvā veḷuparamparāya bandhitvā evamāha—**He then had a bowl carved, put it in a carrying net, hung it at the end of a succession of vertical bamboo poles, and announced,*";
P_HTM[6453]="*“yo samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā arahā ceva iddhimā ca dinnaṃyeva pattaṃ oharatū”ti.**“I will give this bowl to any perfected monastic or brahmin who brings it down by supernormal powers.”*";
P_HTM[6454]="*Atha kho pūraṇo kassapo yena rājagahako seṭṭhi tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā rājagahakaṃ seṭṭhiṃ etadavoca—**Pūraṇa Kassapa went to that merchant and said,*";
P_HTM[6455]="*“ahañhi, gahapati, arahā ceva iddhimā ca, dehi me pattan”ti.**“I’m perfected and have supernormal powers. Give me the bowl.”*";
P_HTM[6456]="*“Sace, bhante, āyasmā arahā ceva iddhimā ca dinnaṃyeva pattaṃ oharatū”ti.**“If you’re perfected and have supernormal powers, then bring it down and it’s yours.”*";
P_HTM[6457]="*Atha kho makkhali gosālo …**The same thing happened with Makkhali Gosāla,*";
P_HTM[6458]="*ajito kesakambalo …**Ajita Kesakambala,*";
P_HTM[6459]="*pakudho kaccāyano …**Pakudha Kaccāyana,*";
P_HTM[6460]="*sañcayo belaṭṭhaputto …**Sañcaya Belaṭṭhaputta,*";
P_HTM[6461]="*nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto yena rājagahako seṭṭhi tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā rājagahakaṃ seṭṭhiṃ etadavoca—**and Nigaṇṭha Nāṭaputta.*";
P_HTM[6462]="*“ahañhi, gahapati, arahā ceva iddhimā ca, dehi me pattan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6463]="*“Sace, bhante, āyasmā arahā ceva iddhimā ca, dinnaṃyeva pattaṃ oharatū”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6464]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā ca mahāmoggallāno āyasmā ca piṇḍolabhāradvājo pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya rājagahaṃ piṇḍāya pavisiṃsu.**Soon afterwards, after robing up in the morning, Venerable Mahāmoggallāna and Venerable Piṇḍola Bhāradvāja took their bowls and robes and entered Rājagaha for alms.*";
P_HTM[6465]="*Atha kho āyasmā piṇḍolabhāradvājo āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ etadavoca—**Piṇḍola Bhāradvāja said to Mahāmoggallāna,*";
P_HTM[6466]="*“āyasmā kho mahāmoggallāno arahā ceva iddhimā ca.**“Venerable, you are perfected and have supernormal powers.*";
P_HTM[6467]="*Gacchāvuso, moggallāna, etaṃ pattaṃ ohara.**If you go and bring down that bowl,*";
P_HTM[6468]="*Tuyheso patto”ti.**it’s yours.”*";
P_HTM[6469]="*“Āyasmā kho bhāradvājo arahā ceva iddhimā ca.**“Venerable, you too are perfected and have supernormal powers.*";
P_HTM[6470]="*Gacchāvuso, bhāradvāja, etaṃ pattaṃ ohara.**If you bring it down,*";
P_HTM[6471]="*Tuyheso patto”ti.**it’s yours.”*";
P_HTM[6472]="*Atha kho āyasmā piṇḍolabhāradvājo vehāsaṃ abbhuggantvā taṃ pattaṃ gahetvā tikkhattuṃ rājagahaṃ anupariyāyi.**Piṇḍola Bhāradvāja then rose up in the air, took hold of that bowl, and circled around Rājagaha three times.*";
P_HTM[6473]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājagahako seṭṭhi saputtadāro sake nivesane ṭhito hoti pañjaliko namassamāno—**Just then that merchant, together with his wives and children, was standing in his own house, raising his joined palms in homage, thinking,*";
P_HTM[6474]="*idheva, bhante, ayyo bhāradvājo amhākaṃ nivesane patiṭṭhātūti.**“May Venerable Piṇḍola Bhāradvāja land right here at our house.”*";
P_HTM[6475]="*Atha kho āyasmā piṇḍolabhāradvājo rājagahakassa seṭṭhissa nivesane patiṭṭhāsi.**And Piṇḍola Bhāradvāja did just that.*";
P_HTM[6476]="*Atha kho rājagahako seṭṭhi āyasmato piṇḍolabhāradvājassa hatthato pattaṃ gahetvā mahagghassa khādanīyassa pūretvā āyasmato piṇḍolabhāradvājassa adāsi.**The merchant then took the bowl from his hands, filled it with expensive fresh foods, and gave it back to Piṇḍola Bhāradvāja,*";
P_HTM[6477]="*Atha kho āyasmā piṇḍolabhāradvājo taṃ pattaṃ gahetvā ārāmaṃ agamāsi.**who then left for the monastery.*";
P_HTM[6478]="*Assosuṃ kho manussā—**People heard*";
P_HTM[6479]="*ayyena kira piṇḍolabhāradvājena rājagahakassa seṭṭhissa patto ohāritoti.**that Piṇḍola Bhāradvāja had taken down the merchant’s bowl,*";
P_HTM[6480]="*Te ca manussā uccāsaddā mahāsaddā āyasmantaṃ piṇḍolabhāradvājaṃ piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhiṃsu.**and making a great uproar, they followed right behind him.*";
P_HTM[6481]="*Assosi kho bhagavā uccāsaddaṃ mahāsaddaṃ;**Hearing all the noise,*";
P_HTM[6482]="*sutvāna āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi—**the Buddha asked Venerable Ānanda what it was,*";
P_HTM[6483]="*“kiṃ nu kho so, ānanda, uccāsaddo mahāsaddo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6484]="*“Āyasmatā, bhante, piṇḍolabhāradvājena rājagahakassa seṭṭhissa patto ohārito.**and Ānanda explained to him all that had happened.*";
P_HTM[6485]="*Assosuṃ kho, bhante, manussā—* **";
P_HTM[6486]="*ayyena kira piṇḍolabhāradvājena rājagahakassa seṭṭhissa patto ohāritoti.* **";
P_HTM[6487]="*Te ca, bhante, manussā uccāsaddā mahāsaddā āyasmantaṃ piṇḍolabhāradvājaṃ piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhā.* **";
P_HTM[6488]="*So eso, bhante, bhagavā uccāsaddo mahāsaddo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6489]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā āyasmantaṃ piṇḍolabhāradvājaṃ paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha of monks gathered and questioned Piṇḍola Bhāradvāja:*";
P_HTM[6490]="*“saccaṃ kira tayā, bhāradvāja, rājagahakassa seṭṭhissa patto ohārito”ti?**“Is it true, Bhāradvāja, that you brought down that merchant’s bowl?”*";
P_HTM[6491]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[6492]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—**The Buddha rebuked him,*";
P_HTM[6493]="*“ananucchavikaṃ, bhāradvāja, ananulomikaṃ appatirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ akaraṇīyaṃ.**“It’s not suitable, Bhāradvāja, it’s not proper, it’s not worthy of a monastic, it’s not allowable, it’s not to be done.*";
P_HTM[6494]="*Kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, bhāradvāja, chavassa dārupattassa kāraṇā gihīnaṃ uttari manussadhammaṃ iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ dassessasi.**How can you show a superhuman ability, a wonder of supernormal power, to householders for the sake of a miserable wooden bowl?*";
P_HTM[6495]="*Seyyathāpi, bhāradvāja, mātugāmo chavassa māsakarūpassa kāraṇā kopinaṃ dasseti;**It’s just like a woman showing her private parts for a miserable _māsaka_ coin.*";
P_HTM[6496]="*evameva kho tayā, bhāradvāja, chavassa dārupattassa kāraṇā gihīnaṃ uttari manussadhammaṃ iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ dassitaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6497]="*Netaṃ, bhāradvāja, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[6498]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after rebuking him …*";
P_HTM[6499]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[6500]="*“na, bhikkhave, gihīnaṃ uttarimanussadhammaṃ iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ dassetabbaṃ.**“You should not show a superhuman ability, a wonder of supernormal power, to householders.*";
P_HTM[6501]="*Yo dasseyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6502]="*Bhindathetaṃ, bhikkhave, dārupattaṃ sakalikaṃ sakalikaṃ katvā, bhikkhūnaṃ añjanupapisanaṃ detha.**Now destroy that wooden bowl and make it into splinters. Give these to the monks to use as scent in ointments.*";
P_HTM[6503]="*Na ca, bhikkhave, dārupatto dhāretabbo.**And you should not use a wooden bowl.*";
P_HTM[6504]="*Yo dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6505]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū uccāvace patte dhārenti sovaṇṇamayaṃ rūpiyamayaṃ.**At that time the monks from the group of six used luxurious bowls made with gold and silver.*";
P_HTM[6506]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6507]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[6508]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6509]="*“Na, bhikkhave, sovaṇṇamayo patto dhāretabbo …pe…**“You should not use an almsbowl made with gold,*";
P_HTM[6510]="*na rūpiyamayo patto dhāretabbo …**silver,*";
P_HTM[6511]="*na maṇimayo patto dhāretabbo …**gems,*";
P_HTM[6512]="*na veḷuriyamayo patto dhāretabbo …**beryl,*";
P_HTM[6513]="*na phalikamayo patto dhāretabbo …**crystal,*";
P_HTM[6514]="*na kaṃsamayo patto dhāretabbo …**bronze,*";
P_HTM[6515]="*na kācamayo patto dhāretabbo …**glass,*";
P_HTM[6516]="*na tipumayo patto dhāretabbo …**tin,*";
P_HTM[6517]="*na sīsamayo patto dhāretabbo …**lead,*";
P_HTM[6518]="*na tambalohamayo patto dhāretabbo.**or copper.*";
P_HTM[6519]="*Yo dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6520]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, dve patte—**I allow two kinds of almsbowls:*";
P_HTM[6521]="*ayopattaṃ, mattikāpattan”ti.**an iron bowl and a ceramic bowl.”*";
P_HTM[6522]="*Tena kho pana samayena pattamūlaṃ ghaṃsiyati.**At that time the bottoms of the bowls became scratched.*";
P_HTM[6523]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6524]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pattamaṇḍalan”ti.**“I allow a circular bowl stand.”*";
P_HTM[6525]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū uccāvacāni pattamaṇḍalāni dhārenti sovaṇṇamayaṃ rūpiyamayaṃ.**Soon afterwards the monks from the group of six used luxurious bowl stands made with gold and silver.*";
P_HTM[6526]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6527]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[6528]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6529]="*“Na, bhikkhave, uccāvacāni pattamaṇḍalāni dhāretabbāni.**“You should not use a luxurious bowl stand.*";
P_HTM[6530]="*Yo dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6531]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, dve pattamaṇḍalāni—**I allow two kinds of bowl stands:*";
P_HTM[6532]="*tipumayaṃ, sīsamayan”ti.**a bowl stand made of tin and a bowl stand made of lead.”*";
P_HTM[6533]="*Bahalāni maṇḍalāni na acchupiyanti.**There were thick bowl stands on which the bowls did not sit properly.*";
P_HTM[6534]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6535]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, likhitun”ti.**“I allow you to carve them out.”*";
P_HTM[6536]="*Valī honti.**There were marks left from the carving.*";
P_HTM[6537]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6538]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, makaradantakaṃ chinditun”ti.**“I allow you to cut a shark-teeth pattern.”*";
P_HTM[6539]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū citrāni pattamaṇḍalāni dhārenti rūpakākiṇṇāni bhittikammakatāni.**Soon the monks from the group of six used bowl stands with colorful patterns, decorated like walls.*";
P_HTM[6540]="*Tāni rathikāyapi dassentā āhiṇḍanti.**As they were walking about, they showed them off in the streets.*";
P_HTM[6541]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6542]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[6543]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6544]="*“Na, bhikkhave, citrāni pattamaṇḍalāni dhāretabbāni rūpakākiṇṇāni bhittikammakatāni.**“You should not use a bowl stand with a colorful pattern, decorated like a wall.*";
P_HTM[6545]="*Yo dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6546]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pakatimaṇḍalan”ti.**I allow an ordinary bowl stand.”*";
P_HTM[6547]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū sodakaṃ pattaṃ paṭisāmenti.**At this time the monks put away their bowls while still wet.*";
P_HTM[6548]="*Patto dussati.**The bowls were stained.*";
P_HTM[6549]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6550]="*“Na, bhikkhave, sodako patto paṭisāmetabbo.**“You should not put away your bowl while still wet.*";
P_HTM[6551]="*Yo paṭisāmeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6552]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, otāpetvā pattaṃ paṭisāmetun”ti.**You should sun your bowl and then put it away.”*";
P_HTM[6553]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū sodakaṃ pattaṃ otāpenti.**Soon afterwards the monks sunned their bowls while still wet.*";
P_HTM[6554]="*Patto duggandho hoti.**The bowls became smelly.*";
P_HTM[6555]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6556]="*“Na, bhikkhave, sodako patto otāpetabbo.**“You should not sun your bowl while still wet.*";
P_HTM[6557]="*Yo otāpeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6558]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, vodakaṃ katvā otāpetvā pattaṃ paṭisāmetun”ti.**You should dry the bowl and then sun it before you put it away.”*";
P_HTM[6559]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū uṇhe pattaṃ nidahanti.**Monks left their bowls in the heat of the sun.*";
P_HTM[6560]="*Pattassa vaṇṇo dussati.**The bowls became discolored.*";
P_HTM[6561]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6562]="*“Na, bhikkhave, uṇhe patto nidahitabbo.**“You should not leave your bowl in the heat of the sun.*";
P_HTM[6563]="*Yo nidaheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6564]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, muhuttaṃ uṇhe otāpetvā pattaṃ paṭisāmetun”ti.**You should sun it in the heat for a short time and then put it away.”*";
P_HTM[6565]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā pattā ajjhokāse anādhārā nikkhittā honti.**On one occasion a number of almsbowls had been put down outside without support.*";
P_HTM[6566]="*Vātamaṇḍalikāya āvaṭṭetvā pattā bhijjiṃsu.**A whirlwind rolled the bowls around and as a result they broke.*";
P_HTM[6567]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6568]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pattādhārakan”ti.**“I allow a bowl rest.”*";
P_HTM[6569]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū miḍḍhante pattaṃ nikkhipanti.**On one occasion the monks had put their bowls on the edge of a bench.*";
P_HTM[6570]="*Paripatitvā patto bhijjati.**They fell down and broke.*";
P_HTM[6571]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6572]="*“Na, bhikkhave, miḍḍhante patto nikkhipitabbo.**“You should not put your almsbowl on the edge of a bench.*";
P_HTM[6573]="*Yo nikkhipeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6574]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū paribhaṇḍante pattaṃ nikkhipanti.**On one occasion the monks had put their bowls on the edge of a shelf.*";
P_HTM[6575]="*Paripatitvā patto bhijjati.**They fell down and broke.*";
P_HTM[6576]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6577]="*“Na, bhikkhave, paribhaṇḍante patto nikkhipitabbo.**“You should not put your almsbowl on the edge of a shelf.*";
P_HTM[6578]="*Yo nikkhipeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6579]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū chamāya pattaṃ nikkujjanti.**At that time the monks put their bowls upside down on the ground.*";
P_HTM[6580]="*Oṭṭho ghaṃsiyati.**The edge of the bowls were scratched.*";
P_HTM[6581]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6582]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tiṇasanthārakan”ti.**“I allow a straw mat.”*";
P_HTM[6583]="*Tiṇasanthārako upacikāhi khajjati.**The straw mat was eaten by termites.*";
P_HTM[6584]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6585]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, coḷakan”ti.**“I allow a cloth.”*";
P_HTM[6586]="*Coḷakaṃ upacikāhi khajjati.**The cloth was eaten by termites.*";
P_HTM[6587]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6588]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pattamāḷakan”ti.**“I allow a pedestal for almsbowls.”*";
P_HTM[6589]="*Pattamāḷako paripatitvā patto bhijjati.**The bowls fell off the pedestals and broke.*";
P_HTM[6590]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6591]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pattakuṇḍolikan”ti.**“I allow a storage container for almsbowls.”*";
P_HTM[6592]="*Pattakuṇḍolikāya patto ghaṃsiyati.**The bowls were scratched in the storage containers.*";
P_HTM[6593]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6594]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pattatthavikan”ti.**“I allow a bowl bag.”*";
P_HTM[6595]="*Aṃsabaddhako na hoti.**There were no shoulder straps.*";
P_HTM[6596]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6597]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, aṃsabaddhakaṃ bandhanasuttakan”ti.**“I allow a shoulder strap and a string for fastening.”*";
P_HTM[6598]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū bhittikhilepi nāgadantakepi pattaṃ laggenti.**At that time the monks hung their bowls from wall pegs.*";
P_HTM[6599]="*Paripatitvā patto bhijjati.**The bowls fell down and broke.*";
P_HTM[6600]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6601]="*“Na, bhikkhave, patto laggetabbo.**“You should not hang up your almsbowl.*";
P_HTM[6602]="*Yo laggeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6603]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū mañce pattaṃ nikkhipanti, satisammosā nisīdantā ottharitvā pattaṃ bhindenti.**At that time the monks put their bowls on their beds. Sitting down absentmindedly, they crushed the bowls, breaking them.*";
P_HTM[6604]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6605]="*“Na, bhikkhave, mañce patto nikkhipitabbo.**“You should not keep your almsbowl on a bed.*";
P_HTM[6606]="*Yo nikkhipeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6607]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū pīṭhe pattaṃ nikkhipanti, satisammosā nisīdantā ottharitvā pattaṃ bhindenti.**At that time the monks put their bowls on their benches. Sitting down absentmindedly, they crushed the bowls, breaking them.*";
P_HTM[6608]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6609]="*“Na, bhikkhave, pīṭhe patto nikkhipitabbo.**“You should not keep your bowl on a bench.*";
P_HTM[6610]="*Yo nikkhipeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6611]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū aṅke pattaṃ nikkhipanti, satisammosā uṭṭhahanti.**At that time the monks put their bowls in their laps. When they got up absentmindedly,*";
P_HTM[6612]="*Paripatitvā patto bhijjati.**the bowls fell down and broke.*";
P_HTM[6613]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6614]="*“Na, bhikkhave, aṅke patto nikkhipitabbo.**“You should not put your bowl in your lap.*";
P_HTM[6615]="*Yo nikkhipeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6616]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū chatte pattaṃ nikkhipanti.**At one time the monks put their bowls on a sunshade.*";
P_HTM[6617]="*Vātamaṇḍalikāya chattaṃ ukkhipiyati paripatitvā patto bhijjati.**A whirlwind lifted up the sunshade, and the bowls fell down and broke.*";
P_HTM[6618]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6619]="*“Na, bhikkhave, chatte patto nikkhipitabbo.**“You should not put your bowl on a sunshade.*";
P_HTM[6620]="*Yo nikkhipeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6621]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū pattahatthā kavāṭaṃ paṇāmenti.**At that time the monks opened doors with a bowl in their hand.*";
P_HTM[6622]="*Kavāṭo āvaṭṭitvā patto bhijjati.**The doors swung back and the bowls broke.*";
P_HTM[6623]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6624]="*“Na, bhikkhave, pattahatthena kavāṭaṃ paṇāmetabbaṃ.**“You should not open a door with an almsbowl in your hand.*";
P_HTM[6625]="*Yo paṇāmeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6626]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū tumbakaṭāhe piṇḍāya caranti.**At that time the monks went on almsround using gourds as bowls.*";
P_HTM[6627]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6628]="*“seyyathāpi titthiyā”ti.**“They are just like the monastics of other religions.”*";
P_HTM[6629]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6630]="*“Na, bhikkhave, tumbakaṭāhe piṇḍāya caritabbaṃ.**“You should not go on almsround using a gourd as a bowl.*";
P_HTM[6631]="*Yo careyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6632]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū ghaṭikaṭāhe piṇḍāya caranti.**At that time the monks went on almsround using waterpots as bowls.*";
P_HTM[6633]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6634]="*“seyyathāpi titthiyā”ti.**“They are just like the monastics of other religions.”*";
P_HTM[6635]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6636]="*“Na, bhikkhave, ghaṭikaṭāhe piṇḍāya caritabbaṃ.**“You should not go on almsround using a water-pot as a bowl.*";
P_HTM[6637]="*Yo careyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6638]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu sabbapaṃsukūliko hoti.**At that time a certain monk who only used discarded things*";
P_HTM[6639]="*So chavasīsassa pattaṃ dhāreti.**used a skull as a bowl.*";
P_HTM[6640]="*Aññatarā itthī passitvā bhītā vissaramakāsi—**A woman who saw this was terrified, screaming,*";
P_HTM[6641]="*“abhuṃ me pisāco vatāyan”ti.**“Oh my God, a demon!”*";
P_HTM[6642]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[6643]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā chavasīsassa pattaṃ dhāressanti, seyyathāpi pisācillikā”ti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics use skulls as bowls? They are just like goblins.”*";
P_HTM[6644]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6645]="*“Na, bhikkhave, chavasīsassa patto dhāretabbo.**“You should not use a skull as a bowl.*";
P_HTM[6646]="*Yo dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6647]="*Na ca, bhikkhave, sabbapaṃsukūlikena bhavitabbaṃ.**And you should not use only discarded things.*";
P_HTM[6648]="*Yo bhaveyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6649]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū calakānipi aṭṭhikānipi ucchiṭṭhodakampi pattena nīharanti.**At that time the monks carried away chewed food remnants, bones, and dirty mouth-rinsing water in their bowls.*";
P_HTM[6650]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6651]="*“yasmiṃ yevime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā bhuñjanti sova nesaṃ paṭiggaho”ti.**“These Sakyan monastics eat from the same thing that they use as a trash can.”*";
P_HTM[6652]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6653]="*“Na bhikkhave, calakāni vā aṭṭhikāni vā ucchiṭṭhodakaṃ vā pattena nīharitabbaṃ.**“You should not carry away chewed food remnants, bones, and dirty mouth-rinsing water in your almsbowl.*";
P_HTM[6654]="*Yo nīhareyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6655]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, paṭiggahan”ti.**I allow trash cans.”*";
P_HTM[6656]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū hatthena vipphāḷetvā cīvaraṃ sibbenti.**At that time the monks tore the cloth to pieces by hand and then sewed robes.*";
P_HTM[6657]="*Cīvaraṃ vilomikaṃ hoti.**The robes were ugly.*";
P_HTM[6658]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6659]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, satthakaṃ namatakan”ti.**“I allow a knife and a felt sheath.”*";
P_HTM[6660]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa daṇḍasatthakaṃ uppannaṃ hoti.**Soon afterwards the Sangha was given a knife with a handle.*";
P_HTM[6661]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6662]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, daṇḍasatthakan”ti.**“I allow a knife with a handle.”*";
P_HTM[6663]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū uccāvace satthakadaṇḍe dhārenti sovaṇṇamayaṃ rūpiyamayaṃ.**At this time the monks from the group of six used luxurious knife handles made with gold and silver.*";
P_HTM[6664]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6665]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[6666]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6667]="*“Na, bhikkhave, uccāvacā satthakadaṇḍā dhāretabbā.**“You should not use a luxurious knife handle.*";
P_HTM[6668]="*Yo dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6669]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, aṭṭhimayaṃ dantamayaṃ visāṇamayaṃ naḷamayaṃ veḷumayaṃ kaṭṭhamayaṃ jatumayaṃ phalamayaṃ lohamayaṃ saṅkhanābhimayan”ti.**I allow a knife handle made of bone, ivory, horn, reed, bamboo, wood, resin, fruit, metal, and shell.”*";
P_HTM[6670]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū kukkuṭapattenapi veḷupesikāyapi cīvaraṃ sibbenti.**At that time the monks used chicken feathers and pieces of bamboo to sew robes.*";
P_HTM[6671]="*Cīvaraṃ dussibbitaṃ hoti.**The robes were badly sewn.*";
P_HTM[6672]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6673]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, sūcin”ti.**“I allow needles.”*";
P_HTM[6674]="*Sūciyo kaṇṇakitāyo honti …pe…**The needles rusted.*";
P_HTM[6675]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, sūcināḷikan”ti.**“I allow a cylinder for the needles.”*";
P_HTM[6676]="*Sūcināḷikāyapi kaṇṇakitāyo honti …pe…**The needles still rusted.*";
P_HTM[6677]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kiṇṇena pūretun”ti.**“I allow you to fill them with powdered yeast.”*";
P_HTM[6678]="*Kiṇṇepi kaṇṇakitāyo honti …pe…**The needles still rusted.*";
P_HTM[6679]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, sattuyā pūretun”ti.**“I allow you to fill them with flour.”*";
P_HTM[6680]="*Sattuyāpi kaṇṇakitāyo honti …pe…**The needles still rusted.*";
P_HTM[6681]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, saritakan”ti.**“I allow stone powder.”*";
P_HTM[6682]="*Saritakepi kaṇṇakitāyo honti …pe…**The needles still rusted.*";
P_HTM[6683]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, madhusitthakena sāretun”ti.**“I allow you to mix it with beeswax.”*";
P_HTM[6684]="*Saritakaṃ paribhijjati …pe…**The stone powder broke apart.*";
P_HTM[6685]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, saritakasipāṭikan”ti.**“I allow a case.”*";
P_HTM[6686]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū tattha tattha khilaṃ nikkhaṇitvā sambandhitvā cīvaraṃ sibbenti.**At that time the monks erected posts here and there, bound them together, and sewed robes.*";
P_HTM[6687]="*Cīvaraṃ vikaṇṇaṃ hoti.**The corners of the robes were deformed.*";
P_HTM[6688]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6689]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kathinaṃ kathinarajjuṃ tattha tattha obandhitvā cīvaraṃ sibbetun”ti.**“I allow a frame and a string. You should tie down the cloth to the frame as required, before sewing the robe.”*";
P_HTM[6690]="*Visame kathinaṃ pattharanti.**They put up the frame on uneven ground.*";
P_HTM[6691]="*Kathinaṃ paribhijjati …pe…**The frame broke.*";
P_HTM[6692]="*“na, bhikkhave, visame kathinaṃ pattharitabbaṃ.**“You should not put up the frame on uneven ground.*";
P_HTM[6693]="*Yo patthareyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6694]="*Chamāya kathinaṃ pattharanti.**They placed the frame on the ground.*";
P_HTM[6695]="*Kathinaṃ paṃsukitaṃ hoti …pe…**The frame became dirty.*";
P_HTM[6696]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tiṇasanthārakan”ti.**“I allow a straw mat.”*";
P_HTM[6697]="*Kathinassa anto jīrati …pe…**The edges of the frame decayed.*";
P_HTM[6698]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, anuvātaṃ paribhaṇḍaṃ āropetun”ti.**“I allow you to add an edge lengthwise and crosswise.”*";
P_HTM[6699]="*Kathinaṃ nappahoti …pe…**The frame was not the right size.*";
P_HTM[6700]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, daṇḍakathinaṃ bidalakaṃ salākaṃ vinandhanarajjuṃ vinandhanasuttaṃ vinandhitvā cīvaraṃ sibbetun”ti.**“I allow an inner frame, folding the straw mat to fit the frame, spacers, strings for tying together, and strings for tying down. After tying it together, you should sew the robe.”*";
P_HTM[6701]="*Suttantarikāyo visamā honti …pe…**The seams were unevenly spaced.*";
P_HTM[6702]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kaḷimbhakan”ti.**“I allow a ruler.”*";
P_HTM[6703]="*Suttā vaṅkā honti …pe…**The seams were not straight.*";
P_HTM[6704]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, moghasuttakan”ti.**“I allow you to make a guide line.”*";
P_HTM[6705]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū adhotehi pādehi kathinaṃ akkamanti.**The monks stepped on the frame with dirty feet.*";
P_HTM[6706]="*Kathinaṃ dussati.**The frame became dirty.*";
P_HTM[6707]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6708]="*“Na, bhikkhave, adhotehi pādehi kathinaṃ akkamitabbaṃ.**“You should not step on the frame with dirty feet.*";
P_HTM[6709]="*Yo akkameyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6710]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū allehi pādehi kathinaṃ akkamanti.**The monks stepped on the frame with wet feet.*";
P_HTM[6711]="*Kathinaṃ dussati.**The frame became dirty.*";
P_HTM[6712]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6713]="*“Na, bhikkhave, allehi pādehi kathinaṃ akkamitabbaṃ.**“You should not step on the frame with wet feet.*";
P_HTM[6714]="*Yo akkameyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6715]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū saupāhanā kathinaṃ akkamanti.**The monks stepped on the frame while wearing sandals.*";
P_HTM[6716]="*Kathinaṃ dussati.**The frame became dirty.*";
P_HTM[6717]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6718]="*“Na, bhikkhave, saupāhanena kathinaṃ akkamitabbaṃ.**“You should not step on the frame while wearing sandals.*";
P_HTM[6719]="*Yo akkameyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6720]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū cīvaraṃ sibbantā aṅguliyā paṭiggaṇhanti.**When sewing robes, the monks received the needles with their fingers.*";
P_HTM[6721]="*Aṅguliyo dukkhā honti.**They hurt their fingers.*";
P_HTM[6722]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6723]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, paṭiggahan”ti.**“I allow a thimble.”*";
P_HTM[6724]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū uccāvace paṭiggahe dhārenti sovaṇṇamayaṃ rūpiyamayaṃ.**Soon the monks from the group of six used luxurious thimbles made of gold and silver.*";
P_HTM[6725]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6726]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[6727]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6728]="*“Na, bhikkhave, uccāvacā paṭiggahā dhāretabbā.**“You should not use a luxurious thimble.*";
P_HTM[6729]="*Yo dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6730]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, aṭṭhimayaṃ …pe…**I allow a thimble made of bone, ivory, horn, reed, bamboo, wood, resin, fruit, metal,*";
P_HTM[6731]="*saṅkhanābhimayan”ti.**and shell.”*";
P_HTM[6732]="*Tena kho pana samayena sūciyopi satthakāpi paṭiggahāpi nassanti.**Needles, knives, and thimbles got lost.*";
P_HTM[6733]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6734]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, āvesanavitthakan”ti.**“I allow a small bowl.”*";
P_HTM[6735]="*Āvesanavitthake samākulā honti.**The small bowls became too full.*";
P_HTM[6736]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6737]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, paṭiggahathavikan”ti.**“I allow a bag for the thimbles.”*";
P_HTM[6738]="*Aṃsabaddhako na hoti.**There was no shoulder strap.*";
P_HTM[6739]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6740]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, aṃsabaddhakaṃ bandhanasuttakan”ti.**“I allow a shoulder strap and a string for fastening.”*";
P_HTM[6741]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū abbhokāse cīvaraṃ sibbantā sītenapi uṇhenapi kilamanti.**When sewing robes outside, the monks were afflicted by cold and heat.*";
P_HTM[6742]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6743]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kathinasālaṃ kathinamaṇḍapan”ti.**“I allow a sewing-shed and a roof-cover under which to sew.”*";
P_HTM[6744]="*Kathinasālā nīcavatthukā hoti, udakena otthariyyati.**They built the sewing-shed on a low base. It was flooded.*";
P_HTM[6745]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6746]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, uccavatthukaṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to make a high base.”*";
P_HTM[6747]="*Cayo paripatati …pe…**The mound collapsed.*";
P_HTM[6748]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cinituṃ tayo caye—**“I allow you to construct three kinds of raised foundations:*";
P_HTM[6749]="*iṭṭhakācayaṃ, silācayaṃ, dārucayan”ti.**a raised foundation of brick, a raised foundation of stone, and a raised foundation of wood.”*";
P_HTM[6750]="*Ārohantā vihaññanti …pe…**It was difficult to get up to the sewing-shed.*";
P_HTM[6751]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tayo sopāne—**“I allow three kinds of stairs:*";
P_HTM[6752]="*iṭṭhakāsopānaṃ, silāsopānaṃ, dārusopānan”ti.**stairs of brick, stairs of stone, and stairs of wood.”*";
P_HTM[6753]="*Ārohantā paripatanti …pe…**People fell down while climbing the stairs.*";
P_HTM[6754]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ālambanabāhan”ti.**“I allow rails.”*";
P_HTM[6755]="*Kathinasālāya tiṇacuṇṇaṃ paripatati …pe…**Grass and dust fell into the sewing-shed.*";
P_HTM[6756]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ogumphetvā ullittāvalittaṃ kātuṃ—**“I allow you to firm up the structure and then plaster it inside and outside, including:*";
P_HTM[6757]="*setavaṇṇaṃ kāḷavaṇṇaṃ gerukaparikammaṃ mālākammaṃ latākammaṃ makaradantakaṃ pañcapaṭikaṃ cīvaravaṃsaṃ cīvararajjukan”ti.**treating with white color, black color, and red ocher; making a garland pattern, a creeper pattern, a shark-teeth pattern, and the fivefold pattern; putting up a bamboo robe rack and a clothesline.”*";
P_HTM[6758]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū cīvaraṃ sibbetvā tattheva kathinaṃ ujjhitvā pakkamanti, undūrehipi upacikāhipi khajjati.**At that time, when the monks had finished sewing a robe, they abandoned the frame right there and left. Rats and termites ate it.*";
P_HTM[6759]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6760]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kathinaṃ saṅgharitun”ti.**“You should fold up the frame.”*";
P_HTM[6761]="*Kathinaṃ paribhijjati …pe…**The frame broke.*";
P_HTM[6762]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, goghaṃsikāya kathinaṃ saṅgharitun”ti.**“You should fold it up with a rod for support.”*";
P_HTM[6763]="*Kathinaṃ viniveṭhiyati …pe…**The frame unfolded.*";
P_HTM[6764]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bandhanarajjun”ti.**“You should tie it up with a rope.”*";
P_HTM[6765]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū kuṭṭepi thambhepi kathinaṃ ussāpetvā pakkamanti.**At that time the monks leaned the frame against a wall or a pillar and left.*";
P_HTM[6766]="*Paripatitvā kathinaṃ bhijjati.**It fell down and broke.*";
P_HTM[6767]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6768]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhittikhile vā nāgadante vā laggetun”ti.**“You should hang it from a wall peg.”*";
P_HTM[6769]="*Atha kho bhagavā rājagahe yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena vesālī tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**When the Buddha had stayed at Rājagaha for as long as he liked, he set out wandering toward Vesālī.*";
P_HTM[6770]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū sūcikampi satthakampi bhesajjampi pattena ādāya gacchanti.**And the monks went, too, after putting their needles, knives, and medicines in their almsbowls.*";
P_HTM[6771]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6772]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhesajjatthavikan”ti.**“I allow a medicine bag.”*";
P_HTM[6773]="*Aṃsabaddhako na hoti …pe…**There was no shoulder strap.*";
P_HTM[6774]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, aṃsabaddhakaṃ bandhanasuttakan”ti.**“I allow a shoulder strap and a string for fastening it.”*";
P_HTM[6775]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu upāhanāyo kāyabandhanena bandhitvā gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**At this time a certain monk bound his sandals to his belt and entered a village for alms.*";
P_HTM[6776]="*Aññataro upāsako taṃ bhikkhuṃ abhivādento upāhanāyo sīsena ghaṭṭeti.**A lay follower who bowed to that monk hit his head against those sandals.*";
P_HTM[6777]="*So bhikkhu maṅku ahosi.**The monk was embarrassed.*";
P_HTM[6778]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**When he had returned to the monastery, he told the monks what had happened,*";
P_HTM[6779]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**and they in turn told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6780]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, upāhanatthavikan”ti.**“I allow a bag for sandals.”*";
P_HTM[6781]="*Aṃsabaddhako na hoti …pe…**There was no shoulder strap.*";
P_HTM[6782]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, aṃsabaddhakaṃ bandhanasuttakan”ti.**“I allow a shoulder strap and a string for fastening it.”*";
P_HTM[6783]="*Tena kho pana samayena antarāmagge udakaṃ akappiyaṃ hoti.**While they were traveling, the water was unallowable to use,*";
P_HTM[6784]="*Parissāvanaṃ na hoti.**but there was no water filter.*";
P_HTM[6785]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6786]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, parissāvanan”ti.**“I allow a water filter.”*";
P_HTM[6787]="*Coḷakaṃ nappahoti …pe…**There was no suitable cloth.*";
P_HTM[6788]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kaṭacchuparissāvanan”ti.**“I allow a filter with a handle.”*";
P_HTM[6789]="*Coḷakaṃ nappahoti …pe…**There was still no suitable cloth.*";
P_HTM[6790]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, dhammakaraṇan”ti.**“I allow a water strainer.”*";
P_HTM[6791]="*Tena kho pana samayena dve bhikkhū kosalesu janapade addhānamaggappaṭipannā honti.**At this time two monks were traveling through the Kosalan country.*";
P_HTM[6792]="*Eko bhikkhu anācāraṃ ācarati.**One monk misbehaved,*";
P_HTM[6793]="*Dutiyo bhikkhu taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—**and the second monk said to him,*";
P_HTM[6794]="*“mā, āvuso, evarūpaṃ akāsi.**“Don’t do that;*";
P_HTM[6795]="*Netaṃ kappatī”ti.**it’s not allowable.”*";
P_HTM[6796]="*So tasmiṃ upanandhi.**Because of that the first monk became resentful.*";
P_HTM[6797]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu pipāsāya pīḷito upanaddhaṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—**Soon afterwards the second monk was very thirsty. He asked the resentful monk*";
P_HTM[6798]="*“dehi me, āvuso, parissāvanaṃ, pānīyaṃ pivissāmī”ti.**to borrow his water filter.*";
P_HTM[6799]="*Upanaddho bhikkhu na adāsi.**He refused,*";
P_HTM[6800]="*So bhikkhu pipāsāya pīḷito kālamakāsi.**and the second monk died from thirst.*";
P_HTM[6801]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**When the resentful monk arrived at the monastery, he told the monks what had happened.*";
P_HTM[6802]="*“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, āvuso, parissāvanaṃ yāciyamāno na adāsī”ti?**“So you refused to lend your water filter when asked?”*";
P_HTM[6803]="*“Evamāvuso”ti.**“Yes.”*";
P_HTM[6804]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[6805]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhu parissāvanaṃ yāciyamāno na dassatī”ti.**“How can a monk act like this?”*";
P_HTM[6806]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6807]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the monks gathered and questioned that monk:*";
P_HTM[6808]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, parissāvanaṃ yāciyamāno na adāsī”ti?**“Is it true, monk, that you acted like this?”*";
P_HTM[6809]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[6810]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—**The Buddha rebuked him,*";
P_HTM[6811]="*“ananucchavikaṃ, moghapurisa, ananulomikaṃ appatirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ akaraṇīyaṃ.**“It’s not suitable, foolish man, it’s not proper, it’s not worthy of a monastic, it’s not allowable, it’s not to be done.*";
P_HTM[6812]="*Kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, parissāvanaṃ yāciyamāno na dassasi.**How can you refuse to lend your water filter when asked?*";
P_HTM[6813]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[6814]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after rebuking him …*";
P_HTM[6815]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[6816]="*“na, bhikkhave, addhānamaggappaṭipannena bhikkhunā parissāvanaṃ yāciyamānena na dātabbaṃ.**“If you’re traveling with a monk and he asks to borrow your water filter, you should lend it.*";
P_HTM[6817]="*Yo na dadeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you don’t, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6818]="*Na ca, bhikkhave, aparissāvanakena addhāno paṭipajjitabbo.**But you should not travel without a water filter.*";
P_HTM[6819]="*Yo paṭipajjeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6820]="*Sace na hoti parissāvanaṃ vā dhammakaraṇo vā, saṅghāṭikaṇṇopi adhiṭṭhātabbo—**If there is no water filter or strainer, you should determine a corner of your robe:*";
P_HTM[6821]="*iminā parissāvetvā pivissāmī”ti.**‘I’ll drink after filtering with this.’”*";
P_HTM[6822]="*Atha kho bhagavā anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena vesālī tadavasari.**The Buddha eventually arrived at Vesālī,*";
P_HTM[6823]="*Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ.**where he stayed in the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood.*";
P_HTM[6824]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū navakammaṃ karonti.**At this time the monks were doing building work,*";
P_HTM[6825]="*Parissāvanaṃ na sammati.**but there were not enough water filters.*";
P_HTM[6826]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6827]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, daṇḍaparissāvanan”ti.**“I allow a water filter of cloth fitted to a wooden framework.”*";
P_HTM[6828]="*Daṇḍaparissāvanaṃ na sammati.**There were still not enough filters.*";
P_HTM[6829]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6830]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ottharakan”ti.**“I allow you to filter by spreading cloth on water.”*";
P_HTM[6831]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū makasehi ubbāḷhā honti.**At this time the monks were troubled by mosquitoes.*";
P_HTM[6832]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6833]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, makasakuṭikan”ti.**“I allow a mosquito tent”*";
P_HTM[6834]="*Tena kho pana samayena vesāliyaṃ paṇītānaṃ bhattānaṃ bhattapaṭipāṭi aṭṭhitā hoti.**At this time in Vesālī people had arranged a succession of fine meals.*";
P_HTM[6835]="*Bhikkhū paṇītāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā abhisannakāyā honti bahvābādhā.**After eating the fine food, the monks’ bodies were full of impurities and they were often sick.*";
P_HTM[6836]="*Atha kho jīvako komārabhacco vesāliṃ agamāsi kenacideva karaṇīyena.**Just then Jīvaka Komārabhacca went to Vesālī on some business*";
P_HTM[6837]="*Addasā kho jīvako komārabhacco bhikkhū abhisannakāye bahvābādhe.**and he saw those monks.*";
P_HTM[6838]="*Disvāna yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**He then went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[6839]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho jīvako komārabhacco bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[6840]="*“etarahi, bhante, bhikkhū abhisannakāyā bahvābādhā.**“At present, Sir, there are monks who are often sick and whose bodies are full of impurities.*";
P_HTM[6841]="*Sādhu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhūnaṃ caṅkamañca jantāgharañca anujānātu.**It would be good if you would allow walking-meditation paths and saunas.*";
P_HTM[6842]="*Evaṃ bhikkhū appābādhā bhavissantī”ti.**In this way the monks will rarely get sick.”*";
P_HTM[6843]="*Atha kho bhagavā jīvakaṃ komārabhaccaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi.**The Buddha then instructed, inspired, and gladdened him with a teaching,*";
P_HTM[6844]="*Atha kho jīvako komārabhacco bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**after which he got up from his seat, bowed, circumambulated the Buddha with his right side toward him, and left.*";
P_HTM[6845]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[6846]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, caṅkamañca jantāgharañcā”ti.**“I allow a walking-meditation path and a sauna.”*";
P_HTM[6847]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū visame caṅkame caṅkamanti.**The monks did walking meditation on an uneven walking path,*";
P_HTM[6848]="*Pādā dukkhā honti.**and as a result their feet hurt.*";
P_HTM[6849]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6850]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, samaṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to even it out.”*";
P_HTM[6851]="*Caṅkamo nīcavatthuko hoti.**They built the walking-meditation path on a low base.*";
P_HTM[6852]="*Udakena otthariyyati …pe…**It was flooded.*";
P_HTM[6853]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, uccavatthukaṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to make a high base.”*";
P_HTM[6854]="*Cayo paripatati …pe…**The mound collapsed.*";
P_HTM[6855]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cinituṃ tayo caye—**“I allow you to construct three kinds of raised foundations:*";
P_HTM[6856]="*iṭṭhakācayaṃ, silācayaṃ, dārucayan”ti.**a raised foundation of brick, a raised foundation of stone, and a raised foundation of wood.”*";
P_HTM[6857]="*Ārohantā vihaññanti …pe…**It was difficult to get up on the walking-meditation path.*";
P_HTM[6858]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tayo sopāne—**“I allow three kinds of stairs:*";
P_HTM[6859]="*iṭṭhakāsopānaṃ, silāsopānaṃ, dārusopānan”ti.**stairs of brick, stairs of stone, and stairs of wood.”*";
P_HTM[6860]="*Ārohantā paripatanti …pe…**People fell down while climbing the stairs.*";
P_HTM[6861]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ālambanabāhan”ti.**“I allow rails.”*";
P_HTM[6862]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū caṅkame caṅkamantā paripatanti.**Doing walking meditation on the walking path, the monks fell off.*";
P_HTM[6863]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6864]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, caṅkamanavedikan”ti.**“I allow railings.”*";
P_HTM[6865]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū ajjhokāse caṅkamantā sītenapi uṇhenapi kilamanti.**Doing walking meditation outside, the monks were afflicted with cold and heat.*";
P_HTM[6866]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6867]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, caṅkamanasālan”ti.**“I allow an indoor walking-meditation path.”*";
P_HTM[6868]="*Caṅkamanasālāyaṃ tiṇacuṇṇaṃ paripatati …pe…**Grass and dust fell into the indoor walking-meditation paths.*";
P_HTM[6869]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ogumphetvā ullittāvalittaṃ kātuṃ—**“I allow you to firm up the structure and then to plaster it inside and outside, including:*";
P_HTM[6870]="*setavaṇṇaṃ kāḷavaṇṇaṃ gerukaparikammaṃ mālākammaṃ latākammaṃ makaradantakaṃ pañcapaṭikaṃ cīvaravaṃsaṃ cīvararajjun”ti.**treating with white color, black color, and red ocher; making a garland pattern, a creeper pattern, a shark-teeth pattern, and the fivefold pattern; putting up a bamboo robe rack and a clothesline.”*";
P_HTM[6871]="*Jantāgharaṃ nīcavatthukaṃ hoti, udakena otthariyyati …pe…**They built the sauna on a low base. It was flooded.*";
P_HTM[6872]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, uccavatthukaṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to make a high base.”*";
P_HTM[6873]="*Cayo paripatati …pe…**The mound collapsed.*";
P_HTM[6874]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cinituṃ tayo caye—**“I allow you to construct three kinds of raised foundations:*";
P_HTM[6875]="*iṭṭhakācayaṃ, silācayaṃ, dārucayan”ti.**a raised foundation of brick, a raised foundation of stone, and a raised foundation of wood.”*";
P_HTM[6876]="*Ārohantā vihaññanti …pe…**It was difficult to get up to the sauna.*";
P_HTM[6877]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tayo sopāne—**“I allow three kinds of stairs:*";
P_HTM[6878]="*iṭṭhakāsopānaṃ, silāsopānaṃ, dārusopānan”ti.**stairs of brick, stairs of stone, and stairs of wood.”*";
P_HTM[6879]="*Ārohantā paripatanti …pe…**People fell down while climbing the stairs.*";
P_HTM[6880]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ālambanabāhan”ti.**“I allow rails.”*";
P_HTM[6881]="*Jantāgharassa kavāṭaṃ na hoti …pe…**The sauna had no door.*";
P_HTM[6882]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kavāṭaṃ piṭṭhasaṅghāṭaṃ udukkhalikaṃ uttarapāsakaṃ aggaḷavaṭṭiṃ kapisīsakaṃ sūcikaṃ ghaṭikaṃ tāḷacchiddaṃ āviñchanachiddaṃ āviñchanarajjun”ti.**“I allow a door, a door frame, a lower hinge, an upper hinge, a bolt-receiving post, a bolt socket, a bolt, an upper bolt, a keyhole, a door-pulling hole, a door-pulling rope.”*";
P_HTM[6883]="*Jantāgharassa kuṭṭapādo jīrati …pe…**The base of the sauna wall rotted.*";
P_HTM[6884]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, maṇḍalikaṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to make an encircling ditch.”*";
P_HTM[6885]="*Jantāgharassa dhūmanettaṃ na hoti …pe…**The sauna had no flue.*";
P_HTM[6886]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, dhūmanettan”ti.**“I allow a flue.”*";
P_HTM[6887]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū khuddake jantāghare majjhe aggiṭṭhānaṃ karonti.**At that time the monks built a fire-place in the middle of a small sauna.*";
P_HTM[6888]="*Upacāro na hoti.**There was no room around the fire-place.*";
P_HTM[6889]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6890]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, khuddake jantāghare ekamantaṃ aggiṭṭhānaṃ kātuṃ, mahallake majjhe”ti.**“In a small sauna, you should make the fire-place to one side, but in a large one in the middle.”*";
P_HTM[6891]="*Jantāghare aggi mukhaṃ ḍahati …pe…**The fire in the sauna burnt their faces.*";
P_HTM[6892]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, mukhamattikan”ti.**“I allow clay for the face.”*";
P_HTM[6893]="*Hatthe mattikaṃ tementi …pe…**They moistened the clay with their hands.*";
P_HTM[6894]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, mattikādoṇikan”ti.**“I allow a trough for the clay.”*";
P_HTM[6895]="*Mattikā duggandhā hoti …pe…**The clay was smelly.*";
P_HTM[6896]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, vāsetun”ti.**“I allow you to add scent.”*";
P_HTM[6897]="*Jantāghare aggi kāyaṃ ḍahati …pe…**The fire in the sauna burnt their bodies.*";
P_HTM[6898]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, udakaṃ atiharitun”ti.**“I allow you to bring water.”*";
P_HTM[6899]="*Pātiyāpi pattenapi udakaṃ atiharanti …pe…**They brought the water in basins and bowls.*";
P_HTM[6900]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, udakaṭṭhānaṃ, udakasarāvakan”ti.**“I allow a place for the water and a water scoop.”*";
P_HTM[6901]="*Jantāgharaṃ tiṇacchadanaṃ na sedeti …pe…**Because the sauna had a grass roof, they did not sweat.*";
P_HTM[6902]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ogumphetvā ullittāvalittaṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to firm up the structure and then to plaster it inside and outside.”*";
P_HTM[6903]="*Jantāgharaṃ cikkhallaṃ hoti …pe…**The sauna became muddy.*";
P_HTM[6904]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, santharituṃ tayo santhare—**“I allow three kinds of floors:*";
P_HTM[6905]="*iṭṭhakāsantharaṃ, silāsantharaṃ, dārusantharan”ti.**a brick floor, a stone floor, and a wooden floor.”*";
P_HTM[6906]="*Cikkhallaṃyeva hoti …pe…**It was still muddy.*";
P_HTM[6907]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, dhovitun”ti.**“You should wash it.”*";
P_HTM[6908]="*Udakaṃ santiṭṭhati …pe…**The water remained.*";
P_HTM[6909]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, udakaniddhamanan”ti.**“I allow a water drain.”*";
P_HTM[6910]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū jantāghare chamāya nisīdanti, gattāni kaṇḍūvanti.**The monks sat on the ground and their limbs became itchy.*";
P_HTM[6911]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6912]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, jantāgharapīṭhan”ti.**“I allow a sauna stool.”*";
P_HTM[6913]="*Tena kho pana samayena jantāgharaṃ aparikkhittaṃ hoti …pe…**At that time the sauna was unenclosed.*";
P_HTM[6914]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, parikkhipituṃ tayo pākāre—**“I allow three kinds of encircling walls:*";
P_HTM[6915]="*iṭṭhakāpākāraṃ, silāpākāraṃ, dārupākāran”ti.**a brick wall, a stone wall, and a wooden wall.”*";
P_HTM[6916]="*Koṭṭhako na hoti …pe…**There was no gateway.*";
P_HTM[6917]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, koṭṭhakan”ti.**“I allow a gateway.”*";
P_HTM[6918]="*Koṭṭhako nīcavatthuko hoti, udakena otthariyyati …pe…**They built the gateway on a low base. It was flooded.*";
P_HTM[6919]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, uccavatthukaṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to make a high base.”*";
P_HTM[6920]="*Cayo paripatati …pe…**The mound collapsed.*";
P_HTM[6921]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cinituṃ tayo caye—**“I allow you to construct three kinds of raised foundations:*";
P_HTM[6922]="*iṭṭhakācayaṃ, silācayaṃ, dārucayan”ti.**a raised foundation of brick, a raised foundation of stone, and a raised foundation of wood.”*";
P_HTM[6923]="*Ārohantā vihaññanti …pe…**It was difficult to get up to the gateway.*";
P_HTM[6924]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tayo sopāne—**“I allow three kinds of stairs:*";
P_HTM[6925]="*iṭṭhakāsopānaṃ, silāsopānaṃ, dārusopānan”ti.**stairs of brick, stairs of stone, and stairs of wood.”*";
P_HTM[6926]="*Ārohantā paripatanti …pe…**People fell down while climbing the stairs.*";
P_HTM[6927]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ālambanabāhan”ti.**“I allow rails.”*";
P_HTM[6928]="*Koṭṭhakassa kavāṭaṃ na hoti …pe…**The gateway had no door.*";
P_HTM[6929]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kavāṭaṃ piṭṭhasaṅghāṭaṃ udukkhalikaṃ uttarapāsakaṃ aggaḷavaṭṭiṃ kapisīsakaṃ sūcikaṃ ghaṭikaṃ tāḷacchiddaṃ āviñchanachiddaṃ āviñchanarajjun”ti.**“I allow a door, a door frame, a lower hinge, an upper hinge, a bolt-receiving post, a bolt socket, a bolt, an upper bolt, a keyhole, a door-pulling hole, and a door-pulling rope.”*";
P_HTM[6930]="*Koṭṭhake tiṇacuṇṇaṃ paripatati …pe…**Grass and dust fell into the gateway.*";
P_HTM[6931]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ogumphetvā ullittāvalittaṃ kātuṃ—**“I allow you to firm up the structure and then plaster it inside and outside, including:*";
P_HTM[6932]="*setavaṇṇaṃ kāḷavaṇṇaṃ gerukaparikammaṃ mālākammaṃ latākammaṃ makaradantakaṃ pañcapaṭikan”ti.**treating with white color, black color, and red ocher; making a garland pattern, a creeper pattern, a shark-teeth pattern, and the fivefold pattern.”*";
P_HTM[6933]="*Pariveṇaṃ cikkhallaṃ hoti …pe…**The precincts were muddy.*";
P_HTM[6934]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, marumbaṃ upakiritun”ti.**“I allow a you to cover it with gravel.”*";
P_HTM[6935]="*Na pariyāpuṇanti …pe…**They were unable to do it.*";
P_HTM[6936]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, padarasilaṃ nikkhipitun”ti.**“I allow you to lay down paving stones.”*";
P_HTM[6937]="*Udakaṃ santiṭṭhati …pe…**The water remained.*";
P_HTM[6938]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, udakaniddhamanan”ti.**“I allow a water drain.”*";
P_HTM[6939]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū naggā naggaṃ abhivādenti …pe…**At that time naked monks bowed down to other naked monks …*";
P_HTM[6940]="*naggā naggaṃ abhivādāpenti, naggā naggassa parikammaṃ karonti, naggā naggassa parikammaṃ kārāpenti, naggā naggassa denti, naggā paṭiggaṇhanti, naggā khādanti, naggā bhuñjanti, naggā sāyanti, naggā pivanti.**naked monks had other naked monks bow down to them … naked monks did services for other naked monks … naked monks had other naked monks do services for them … naked monks gave to other naked monks … naked monks received … they ate fresh foods while naked … they ate cooked foods while naked … they ate other foods while naked … they drank while naked.*";
P_HTM[6941]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6942]="*“Na, bhikkhave, naggena naggo abhivādetabbo …pe…**“One who is naked should not bow down to one who is naked,*";
P_HTM[6943]="*na naggena abhivādetabbaṃ …**should not bow down to anyone,*";
P_HTM[6944]="*na naggena naggo abhivādāpetabbo …**should not have a naked monk bow down to him,*";
P_HTM[6945]="*na naggena abhivādāpetabbaṃ …**should not have anyone bow down to him,*";
P_HTM[6946]="*na naggena naggassa parikammaṃ kātabbaṃ …**should not do services for a naked monk,*";
P_HTM[6947]="*na naggena naggassa parikammaṃ kārāpetabbaṃ …**should not have a naked monk do services for him,*";
P_HTM[6948]="*na naggena naggassa dātabbaṃ …**should not give to a naked monk,*";
P_HTM[6949]="*na naggena paṭiggahetabbaṃ …**should not receive,*";
P_HTM[6950]="*na naggena khāditabbaṃ …**should not eat fresh foods,*";
P_HTM[6951]="*na naggena bhuñjitabbaṃ …**should not eat cooked food,*";
P_HTM[6952]="*na naggena sāyitabbaṃ …**should not eat anything,*";
P_HTM[6953]="*na naggena pātabbaṃ.**and should not drink.*";
P_HTM[6954]="*Yo piveyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[6955]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū jantāghare chamāya cīvaraṃ nikkhipanti.**At that time the monks put their robes on the ground in the sauna.*";
P_HTM[6956]="*Cīvaraṃ paṃsukitaṃ hoti.**The robes became dirty.*";
P_HTM[6957]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6958]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cīvaravaṃsaṃ cīvararajjun”ti.**“I allow a bamboo robe rack and a clothesline.”*";
P_HTM[6959]="*Deve vassante cīvaraṃ ovassati …pe…**It rained and the robes became wet.*";
P_HTM[6960]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, jantāgharasālan”ti.**“I allow a sauna shed.”*";
P_HTM[6961]="*Jantāgharasālā nīcavatthukā hoti, udakena otthariyyati …pe…**They built the sauna shed on a low base. It was flooded.*";
P_HTM[6962]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, uccavatthukaṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to make a high base.”*";
P_HTM[6963]="*Cayo paripatati …pe…**The mound collapsed.*";
P_HTM[6964]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cinituṃ …pe…**“I allow you to construct three kinds of raised foundations: a raised foundation of brick, a raised foundation of stone, and a raised foundation of wood.”*";
P_HTM[6965]="*ārohantā vihaññanti …pe…**It was difficult to get up to the sauna shed.*";
P_HTM[6966]="*ārohantā paripatanti …pe…**People fell down while climbing the stairs.*";
P_HTM[6967]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ālambanabāhan”ti.**“I allow rails.”*";
P_HTM[6968]="*Jantāgharasālāya tiṇacuṇṇaṃ paripatati …pe…**Grass and dust fell into the sauna shed.*";
P_HTM[6969]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ogumphetvā ullittāvalittaṃ kātuṃ …pe…**“I allow you to firm up the structure and then to plaster it inside and outside, including: treating with white color, black color, and red ocher; making a garland pattern, a creeper pattern, a shark-teeth pattern, and the fivefold pattern;*";
P_HTM[6970]="*cīvaravaṃsaṃ cīvararajjun”ti.**putting up a bamboo robe rack and a clothesline.”*";
P_HTM[6971]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū jantāgharepi udakepi parikammaṃ kātuṃ kukkuccāyanti.**Being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not do services for one another either in the sauna or in the water.*";
P_HTM[6972]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6973]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tisso paṭicchādiyo—**“I allow you to regard three things as a ‘covering’:*";
P_HTM[6974]="*jantāgharapaṭicchādiṃ, udakapaṭicchādiṃ, vatthapaṭicchādin”ti.**a sauna, water, and a cloth.”*";
P_HTM[6975]="*Tena kho pana samayena jantāghare udakaṃ na hoti.**On one occasion there was no water in the sauna.*";
P_HTM[6976]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6977]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, udapānan”ti.**“I allow a well.”*";
P_HTM[6978]="*Udapānassa kūlaṃ lujjati …pe…**The edge of the well collapsed.*";
P_HTM[6979]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cinituṃ tayo caye—**“I allow you to construct three kinds of foundations:*";
P_HTM[6980]="*iṭṭhakācayaṃ, silācayaṃ, dārucayan”ti.**a foundation of brick, a foundation of stone, and a foundation of wood.”*";
P_HTM[6981]="*Udapāno nīcavatthuko hoti, udakena otthariyyati …pe…**The well was situated on a low site. It was flooded.*";
P_HTM[6982]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, uccavatthukaṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to make a high base.”*";
P_HTM[6983]="*Cayo paripatati …pe…**The mound collapsed.*";
P_HTM[6984]="*ārohantā vihaññanti …pe…**It was difficult to get up to the well.*";
P_HTM[6985]="*ārohantā paripatanti …pe…**People fell down while climbing the stairs.*";
P_HTM[6986]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ālambanabāhan”ti.**“I allow rails.”*";
P_HTM[6987]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū vallikāyapi kāyabandhanenapi udakaṃ vāhenti.**At that time the monks used creepers and belts to haul water.*";
P_HTM[6988]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6989]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, udakavāhanarajjun”ti.**“I allow a water-hauling rope.”*";
P_HTM[6990]="*Hatthā dukkhā honti …pe…**It hurt their hands.*";
P_HTM[6991]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tulaṃ karakaṭakaṃ cakkavaṭṭakan”ti.**“I allow a well-sweep, a pulley, and well-wheels.”*";
P_HTM[6992]="*Bhājanā bahū bhijjanti …pe…**Many vessels broke.*";
P_HTM[6993]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tayo vārake—**“I allow three kinds of buckets:*";
P_HTM[6994]="*lohavārakaṃ, dāruvārakaṃ, cammakkhaṇḍan”ti.**an iron bucket, a wooden bucket, and a bucket made of hide.”*";
P_HTM[6995]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū ajjhokāse udakaṃ vāhentā sītenapi uṇhenapi kilamanti.**While hauling water outside, the monks were afflicted by cold and heat.*";
P_HTM[6996]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6997]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, udapānasālan”ti.**“I allow a well house.”*";
P_HTM[6998]="*Udapānasālāya tiṇacuṇṇaṃ paripatati …pe…**Grass and dust fell into the well house.*";
P_HTM[6999]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ogumphetvā ullittāvalittaṃ kātuṃ—**“I allow you to firm up the structure and then plaster it inside and outside, including:*";
P_HTM[7000]="*setavaṇṇaṃ kāḷavaṇṇaṃ gerukaparikammaṃ mālākammaṃ latākammaṃ makaradantakaṃ pañcapaṭikaṃ cīvaravaṃsaṃ cīvararajjun”ti.**treating with white color, black color, and red ocher; making a garland pattern, a creeper pattern, a shark-teeth pattern, and the fivefold pattern; putting up a bamboo robe rack and a clothesline.”*";
P_HTM[7001]="*Udapāno apāruto hoti, tiṇacuṇṇehipi paṃsukehipi okiriyyati …pe…**The well was not covered. Grass, dust, and dirt fell into it.*";
P_HTM[7002]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, apidhānan”ti.**“I allow a lid.”*";
P_HTM[7003]="*Udakabhājanaṃ na saṃvijjati …pe…**There was no vessel for the water.*";
P_HTM[7004]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, udakadoṇiṃ udakakaṭāhan”ti.**“I allow a water-trough and a water-bowl.”*";
P_HTM[7005]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū ārāme tahaṃ tahaṃ nahāyanti.**At that time the monks bathed here and there in the monastery.*";
P_HTM[7006]="*Ārāmo cikkhallo hoti.**The monastery became muddy.*";
P_HTM[7007]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7008]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, candanikan”ti.**“I allow a waste-water collection tank.”*";
P_HTM[7009]="*Candanikā pākaṭā hoti.**The tank was unenclosed.*";
P_HTM[7010]="*Bhikkhū hiriyanti nahāyituṃ …pe…**The monks were embarrassed to wash there.*";
P_HTM[7011]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, parikkhipituṃ tayo pākāre—**“I allow three kinds of encircling walls:*";
P_HTM[7012]="*iṭṭhakāpākāraṃ, silāpākāraṃ, dārupākāran”ti.**a brick wall, a stone wall, and a wooden wall.”*";
P_HTM[7013]="*Candanikā cikkhallā hoti …pe…**The area became muddy.*";
P_HTM[7014]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, santharituṃ tayo santhare—**“I allow three kinds of decking:*";
P_HTM[7015]="*iṭṭhakāsantharaṃ, silāsantharaṃ, dārusantharan”ti.**a brick decking, a stone decking, and a wooden decking.”*";
P_HTM[7016]="*Udakaṃ santiṭṭhati …pe…**The water remained.*";
P_HTM[7017]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, udakaniddhamanan”ti.**“I allow a water drain.”*";
P_HTM[7018]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhūnaṃ gattāni sītigatāni honti.**The monks were cold.*";
P_HTM[7019]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…* **";
P_HTM[7020]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, udakapuñchaniṃ coḷakenapi paccuddharitun”ti.**“I allow a water wiper and a cloth to dry yourselves with.”*";
P_HTM[7021]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro upāsako saṅghassa atthāya pokkharaṇiṃ kāretukāmo hoti.**On one occasion a lay follower wanted to build a lotus bathing tank for the benefit of the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[7022]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7023]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pokkharaṇin”ti.**“I allow lotus bathing tanks.”*";
P_HTM[7024]="*Pokkharaṇiyā kūlaṃ lujjati …pe…**The edges of the tank collapsed.*";
P_HTM[7025]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cinituṃ tayo caye—**“I allow you to construct three kinds of foundations:*";
P_HTM[7026]="*iṭṭhakācayaṃ, silācayaṃ, dārucayan”ti.**a foundation of brick, a foundation of stone, and a foundation of wood.”*";
P_HTM[7027]="*Ārohantā vihaññanti …pe…**It was difficult to get up to the tank.*";
P_HTM[7028]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tayo sopāne—**“I allow three kinds of stairs:*";
P_HTM[7029]="*iṭṭhakāsopānaṃ, silāsopānaṃ, dārusopānan”ti.**stairs of brick, stairs of stone, and stairs of wood.”*";
P_HTM[7030]="*Ārohantā paripatanti …pe…**People fell down while climbing the stairs.*";
P_HTM[7031]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ālambanabāhan”ti.**“I allow rails.”*";
P_HTM[7032]="*Pokkharaṇiyā udakaṃ purāṇaṃ hoti …pe…**The water in the tanks became stagnant.*";
P_HTM[7033]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, udakamātikaṃ udakaniddhamanan”ti.**“I allow a channel and a drain.”*";
P_HTM[7034]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu saṅghassa atthāya nillekhaṃ jantāgharaṃ kattukāmo hoti.**On one occasion a lay follower wanted to build a sauna with a pointed roof for the benefit of the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[7035]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…* **";
P_HTM[7036]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, nillekhaṃ jantāgharan”ti.**“I allow a sauna with a pointed roof.”*";
P_HTM[7037]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū cātumāsaṃ nisīdanena vippavasanti.**At one time the monks from the group of six did not have sitting mats for four months.*";
P_HTM[7038]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7039]="*“na, bhikkhave, cātumāsaṃ nisīdanena vippavasitabbaṃ.**“You should not be without a sitting mat for four months.*";
P_HTM[7040]="*Yo vippavaseyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you are, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7041]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū pupphābhikiṇṇesu sayanesu sayanti.**At that time the monks from the group of six slept in beds covered in flowers.*";
P_HTM[7042]="*Manussā vihāracārikaṃ āhiṇḍantā passitvā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**When people walking about the dwellings saw this, they complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7043]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[7044]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7045]="*“Na, bhikkhave, pupphābhikiṇṇesu sayanesu sayitabbaṃ.**“You should not sleep in a bed covered in flowers.*";
P_HTM[7046]="*Yo sayeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7047]="*Tena kho pana samayena manussā gandhampi mālampi ādāya ārāmaṃ āgacchanti.**People took scents and garlands and went to the monastery.*";
P_HTM[7048]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā na paṭiggaṇhanti.**Being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not accept.*";
P_HTM[7049]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7050]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gandhaṃ gahetvā kavāṭe pañcaṅgulikaṃ dātuṃ, pupphaṃ gahetvā vihāre ekamantaṃ nikkhipitun”ti.**“I allow you to accept scent to make the five-finger mark on your door, and to accept flowers to place them to one side in your dwelling.”*";
P_HTM[7051]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa namatakaṃ uppannaṃ hoti.**On one occasion the Sangha was given a piece of felt.*";
P_HTM[7052]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7053]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, namatakan”ti.**“I allow felt.”*";
P_HTM[7054]="*Atha kho bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The monks thought,*";
P_HTM[7055]="*“namatakaṃ adhiṭṭhātabbaṃ nu kho udāhu vikappetabban”ti …pe…**“Should it be determined or transferred to another?”*";
P_HTM[7056]="*“na, bhikkhave, namatakaṃ adhiṭṭhātabbaṃ, na vikappetabban”ti.**“It should neither be determined nor transferred to another.”*";
P_HTM[7057]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū āsittakūpadhāne bhuñjanti.**The monks from the group of six ate food from a heating device.*";
P_HTM[7058]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7059]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[7060]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…* **";
P_HTM[7061]="*“na, bhikkhave, āsittakūpadhāne bhuñjitabbaṃ.**“You should not eat food from a heating device.*";
P_HTM[7062]="*Yo bhuñjeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7063]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu gilāno hoti.**On one occasion a certain monk who was sick*";
P_HTM[7064]="*So bhuñjamāno na sakkoti hatthena pattaṃ sandhāretuṃ.**was unable to hold his bowl with his hands while eating.*";
P_HTM[7065]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7066]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, maḷorikan”ti.**“I allow a stand.”*";
P_HTM[7067]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū ekabhājanepi bhuñjanti …pe…**At that time the monks from the group of six ate from the same vessel,*";
P_HTM[7068]="*ekathālakepi pivanti, ekamañcepi tuvaṭṭenti, ekattharaṇāpi tuvaṭṭenti, ekapāvuraṇāpi tuvaṭṭenti, ekattharaṇapāvuraṇāpi tuvaṭṭenti.**drank from the same vessel, and lay down on the same bed, on the same sheet, under the same cover, and both on the same sheet and under the same cover.*";
P_HTM[7069]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7070]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[7071]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7072]="*“Na, bhikkhave, ekabhājane bhuñjitabbaṃ …pe…**“You should not eat from the same vessel,*";
P_HTM[7073]="*na ekathālake pātabbaṃ …**drink from the same vessel,*";
P_HTM[7074]="*na ekamañce tuvaṭṭitabbaṃ …**lie down on the same bed,*";
P_HTM[7075]="*na ekattharaṇā tuvaṭṭitabbaṃ …**lie down on the same sheet,*";
P_HTM[7076]="*na ekapāvuraṇā tuvaṭṭitabbaṃ …**lie down under the same cover,*";
P_HTM[7077]="*na ekattharaṇapāvuraṇā tuvaṭṭitabbaṃ.**or lie down both on the same sheet and under the same cover.*";
P_HTM[7078]="*Yo tuvaṭṭeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7079]="*Tena kho pana samayena vaḍḍho licchavī mettiyabhūmajakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ sahāyo hoti.**At one time Vaḍḍha the Licchavī was a friend of the monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka.*";
P_HTM[7080]="*Atha kho vaḍḍho licchavī yena mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā mettiyabhūmajake bhikkhū etadavoca—**On one occasion he went to them and said,*";
P_HTM[7081]="*“vandāmi, ayyā”ti.**“I pay respect to you, Venerables.”*";
P_HTM[7082]="*Evaṃ vutte, mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū nālapiṃsu.**But they did not respond.*";
P_HTM[7083]="*Dutiyampi kho vaḍḍho licchavī mettiyabhūmajake bhikkhū etadavoca—**A second time*";
P_HTM[7084]="*“vandāmi, ayyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7085]="*Dutiyampi kho mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū nālapiṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[7086]="*Tatiyampi kho vaḍḍho licchavī mettiyabhūmajake bhikkhū etadavoca—**and a third time he said the same thing,*";
P_HTM[7087]="*“vandāmi, ayyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7088]="*Tatiyampi kho mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū nālapiṃsu.**but they still did not respond.*";
P_HTM[7089]="*“Kyāhaṃ ayyānaṃ aparajjhāmi, kissa maṃ ayyā nālapantī”ti?**“Have I done something wrong? Why don’t you respond?”*";
P_HTM[7090]="*“Tathā hi pana tvaṃ, āvuso vaḍḍha, amhe dabbena mallaputtena viheṭhiyamāne ajjhupekkhasī”ti.**“It’s because we’ve been treated badly by Dabba the Mallian and you’re not taking an interest.”*";
P_HTM[7091]="*“Kyāhaṃ, ayyā, karomī”ti?**“What can I do?”*";
P_HTM[7092]="*“Sace kho tvaṃ, āvuso vaḍḍha, iccheyyāsi, ajjeva bhagavā āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ nāsāpeyyā”ti.**“If you like, you could make the Buddha expel Dabba.”*";
P_HTM[7093]="*“Kyāhaṃ, ayyā, karomi, kiṃ mayā sakkā kātun”ti?**“What should I do? How am I able to do that?”*";
P_HTM[7094]="*“Ehi tvaṃ, āvuso vaḍḍha, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkama, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ evaṃ vadehi—**“Go to the Buddha and say,*";
P_HTM[7095]="*‘idaṃ, bhante, nacchannaṃ nappatirūpaṃ.**‘Sir, this is not proper or appropriate.*";
P_HTM[7096]="*Yāyaṃ, bhante, disā abhayā anītikā anupaddavā sāyaṃ disā sabhayā saītikā saupaddavā;**There’s fear, distress, and oppression in this district, where none of these should exist.*";
P_HTM[7097]="*yato nivātaṃ tato savātaṃ;**From where one would expect security, there’s insecurity.*";
P_HTM[7098]="*udakaṃ maññe ādittaṃ;**It’s as if water is burning.*";
P_HTM[7099]="*ayyena me dabbena mallaputtena pajāpati dūsitā’”ti.**Venerable Dabba the Mallian has raped my wife.’”*";
P_HTM[7100]="*“Evaṃ, ayyā”ti kho vaḍḍho licchavī mettiyabhūmajakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Saying, “Yes,” he went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[7101]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho vaḍḍho licchavī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and repeated*";
P_HTM[7102]="*“idaṃ, bhante, nacchannaṃ nappatirūpaṃ.**what he had been told to say.*";
P_HTM[7103]="*Yāyaṃ, bhante, disā abhayā anītikā anupaddavā sāyaṃ disā sabhayā saītikā saupaddavā;* **";
P_HTM[7104]="*yato nivātaṃ tato savātaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[7105]="*udakaṃ maññe ādittaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[7106]="*ayyena me dabbena mallaputtena pajāpati dūsitā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7107]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned Dabba:*";
P_HTM[7108]="*“sarasi tvaṃ, dabba, evarūpaṃ kattā yathāyaṃ vaḍḍho āhā”ti?**“Dabba, do you remember doing as Vaḍḍha says?”*";
P_HTM[7109]="*“Yathā maṃ, bhante, bhagavā jānātī”ti.**“Venerable Sir, you know what I’m like.”*";
P_HTM[7110]="*Dutiyampi kho bhagavā …pe…**A second*";
P_HTM[7111]="*tatiyampi kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ etadavoca—**and a third time the Buddha asked the same question*";
P_HTM[7112]="*“sarasi tvaṃ, dabba, evarūpaṃ kattā yathāyaṃ vaḍḍho āhā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[7113]="*“Yathā maṃ, bhante, bhagavā jānātī”ti.**and got the same response.*";
P_HTM[7114]="*“Na kho, dabba, dabbā evaṃ nibbeṭhenti.**He then said, “Dabba, the Dabbas don’t give such evasive answers.*";
P_HTM[7115]="*Sace tayā kataṃ, katanti vadehi;**If it was done by you, say so;*";
P_HTM[7116]="*sace akataṃ, akatanti vadehī”ti.**if it wasn’t done by you, then say that.”*";
P_HTM[7117]="*“Yato ahaṃ, bhante, jāto nābhijānāmi supinantenapi methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevitā, pageva jāgaro”ti.**“Since I was born, Sir, I don’t recall having sexual intercourse even in a dream, let alone when awake.”*";
P_HTM[7118]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi—**And the Buddha addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[7119]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho vaḍḍhassa licchavissa pattaṃ nikkujjatu, asambhogaṃ saṅghena karotu.**“Well then, monks, the Sangha should overturn the almsbowl against Vaḍḍha the Licchavī, prohibiting him from interacting with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[7120]="*Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa upāsakassa patto nikkujjitabbo—**When a lay follower has eight qualities, you should overturn your bowl against him:*";
P_HTM[7121]="*bhikkhūnaṃ alābhāya parisakkati, bhikkhūnaṃ anatthāya parisakkati, bhikkhūnaṃ avāsāya parisakkati, bhikkhū akkosati paribhāsati, bhikkhū bhikkhūhi bhedeti, buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati.**he’s trying to stop monks from acquiring material gains; he’s trying to harm monks; he’s trying to get monks to lose their place of residence; he abuses and reviles monks; he causes division between monks; he disparages the Buddha; he disparages the Teaching; he disparages the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[7122]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, imehi aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgatassa upāsakassa pattaṃ nikkujjituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7123]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nikkujjitabbo.**And the overturning of the bowl is to be done like this.*";
P_HTM[7124]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[7125]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[7126]="*Vaḍḍho licchavī āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā anuddhaṃseti.**Vaḍḍha the Licchavī is groundlessly charging Venerable Dabba the Mallian with failure in morality.*";
P_HTM[7127]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho vaḍḍhassa licchavissa pattaṃ nikkujjeyya, asambhogaṃ saṅghena kareyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should overturn the bowl against Vaḍḍha the Licchavī, prohibiting him from interacting with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[7128]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[7129]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[7130]="*Vaḍḍho licchavī āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā anuddhaṃseti.**Vaḍḍha the Licchavī is groundlessly charging Venerable Dabba the Mallian with failure in morality.*";
P_HTM[7131]="*Saṅgho vaḍḍhassa licchavissa pattaṃ nikkujjati, asambhogaṃ saṅghena karoti.**The Sangha overturns the bowl against Vaḍḍha the Licchavī, prohibiting him from interacting with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[7132]="*Yassāyasmato khamati vaḍḍhassa licchavissa pattassa nikkujjanā, asambhogaṃ saṅghena karaṇaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of overturning the bowl against Vaḍḍha the Licchavī, prohibiting him from interacting with the Sangha, should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[7133]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[7134]="*Nikkujjito saṅghena vaḍḍhassa licchavissa patto, asambhogo saṅghena.**The Sangha has overturned the bowl against Vaḍḍha the Licchavī, prohibiting him from interacting with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[7135]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[7136]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena vaḍḍhassa licchavissa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā vaḍḍhaṃ licchaviṃ etadavoca—**After robing up the following morning, Venerable Ānanda took his bowl and robe, went to the house of Vaḍḍha the Licchavī, and told him,*";
P_HTM[7137]="*“saṅghena te, āvuso vaḍḍha, patto nikkujjito.**“Vaḍḍha, the Sangha has overturned the bowl against you.*";
P_HTM[7138]="*Asambhogosi saṅghenā”ti.**You’re prohibited from interacting with the Sangha.”*";
P_HTM[7139]="*Atha kho vaḍḍho licchavī—**As a result,*";
P_HTM[7140]="*saṅghena kira me patto nikkujjito, asambhogomhi kira saṅghenāti—* **";
P_HTM[7141]="*tattheva mucchito papato.**Vaḍḍha fainted right there.*";
P_HTM[7142]="*Atha kho vaḍḍhassa licchavissa mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā vaḍḍhaṃ licchaviṃ etadavocuṃ—**But Vaḍḍha’s friends and relatives said to him,*";
P_HTM[7143]="*“alaṃ, āvuso vaḍḍha, mā soci, mā paridevi.**“Don’t be sad, Vaḍḍha.*";
P_HTM[7144]="*Mayaṃ bhagavantaṃ pasādessāma bhikkhusaṅghañcā”ti.**We’ll reconcile you with the Buddha and the Sangha of monks.”*";
P_HTM[7145]="*Atha kho vaḍḍho licchavī saputtadāro samittāmacco sañātisālohito allavattho allakeso yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato pādesu sirasā nipatitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**Soon afterwards Vaḍḍha, together with his wives and children, together with his friends and relatives, with wet clothes and wet hair, went to the Buddha. He bowed down at the Buddha’s feet and said,*";
P_HTM[7146]="*“accayo maṃ, bhante, accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ, yohaṃ ayyaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā anuddhaṃsesiṃ.**“Sir, I’ve made a mistake. I’ve been foolish, confused, and unskillful.*";
P_HTM[7147]="*Tassa me, bhante, bhagavā accayaṃ accayato paṭiggaṇhātu āyatiṃ saṃvarāyā”ti.**Please forgive me so that I may restrain myself in the future.”*";
P_HTM[7148]="*“Taggha tvaṃ, āvuso vaḍḍha, accayo accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ, yaṃ tvaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā anuddhaṃsesi.**“You have certainly made a mistake. You’ve been foolish, confused, and unskillful.*";
P_HTM[7149]="*Yato ca kho tvaṃ, āvuso vaḍḍha, accayaṃ accayato disvā yathādhammaṃ paṭikarosi, taṃ te mayaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma.**But since you acknowledge your mistake and make proper amends, I forgive you.*";
P_HTM[7150]="*Vuḍḍhihesā, āvuso vaḍḍha, ariyassa vinaye yo accayaṃ accayato disvā yathādhammaṃ paṭikaroti, āyatiṃ saṃvaraṃ āpajjatī”ti.**For this is called growth in the training of the noble ones: acknowledging a mistake, making proper amends, and undertaking restraint for the future.”*";
P_HTM[7151]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi—**The Buddha then addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[7152]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho vaḍḍhassa licchavissa pattaṃ ukkujjatu, sambhogaṃ saṅghena karotu.**“Well then, the Sangha should turn the almsbowl upright for Vaḍḍha the Licchavī, allowing him to interact with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[7153]="*Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatassa upāsakassa patto ukkujjitabbo—**When a lay follower has eight qualities, you should turn your bowl upright for him:*";
P_HTM[7154]="*na bhikkhūnaṃ alābhāya parisakkati, na bhikkhūnaṃ anatthāya parisakkati, na bhikkhūnaṃ avāsāya parisakkati, na bhikkhū akkosati paribhāsati, na bhikkhū bhikkhūhi bhedeti, na buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, na dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, na saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati.**he is not trying to stop monks from acquiring material gains; he is not trying to harm monks; he is not trying to get monks to lose their place of residence; he doesn’t abuse or revile monks; he doesn’t cause division between monks; he doesn’t disparage the Buddha; he doesn’t disparage the Teaching; he doesn’t disparage the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[7155]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, imehi aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgatassa upāsakassa pattaṃ ukkujjituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7156]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, ukkujjitabbo.**And the turning of the bowl upright is to be done like this.*";
P_HTM[7157]="*Tena, bhikkhave, vaḍḍhena licchavinā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**Vaḍḍha the Licchavī should approach the Sangha, put his upper robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and say:*";
P_HTM[7158]="*‘saṅghena me, bhante, patto nikkujjito, asambhogomhi saṅghena.**‘Venerables, the Sangha has overturned the bowl against me, prohibiting me from interacting with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[7159]="*Sohaṃ, bhante, sammā vattāmi, lomaṃ pātemi, netthāraṃ vattāmi, saṅghaṃ pattukkujjanaṃ yācāmī’ti.**I’m conducting myself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released. I ask the Sangha to turn the bowl upright for me.’*";
P_HTM[7160]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbo.**And he should ask a second*";
P_HTM[7161]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbo.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[7162]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[7163]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[7164]="*Saṅghena vaḍḍhassa licchavissa patto nikkujjito, asambhogo saṅghena.**The Sangha had overturned the bowl against Vaḍḍha the Licchavī, prohibiting him from interacting with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[7165]="*So sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, saṅghaṃ pattukkujjanaṃ yācati.**He is now conducting himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and is asking the Sangha to turn the bowl upright for him.*";
P_HTM[7166]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho vaḍḍhassa licchavissa pattaṃ ukkujjeyya, sambhogaṃ saṅghena kareyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should turn the bowl upright for Vaḍḍha the Licchavī, allowing him to interact with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[7167]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[7168]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[7169]="*Saṅghena vaḍḍhassa licchavissa patto nikkujjito, asambhogo saṅghena.**The Sangha had overturned the bowl against Vaḍḍha the Licchavī, prohibiting him from interacting with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[7170]="*So sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, saṅghaṃ pattukkujjanaṃ yācati.**He is now conducting himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and is asking the Sangha to turn the bowl upright for him.*";
P_HTM[7171]="*Saṅgho vaḍḍhassa licchavissa pattaṃ ukkujjati, sambhogaṃ saṅghena karoti.**The Sangha turns the bowl upright for Vaḍḍha the Licchavī, allowing him to interact with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[7172]="*Yassāyasmato khamati vaḍḍhassa licchavissa pattassa ukkujjanā, sambhogaṃ saṅghena karaṇaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of turning the bowl upright for Vaḍḍha the Licchavī, allowing him to interact with the Sangha, should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[7173]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[7174]="*Ukkujjito saṅghena vaḍḍhassa licchavissa patto, sambhogo saṅghena.**The Sangha has turned the bowl upright for Vaḍḍha the Licchavī, allowing him to interact with the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[7175]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[7176]="*Atha kho bhagavā vesāliyaṃ yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena bhaggā tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**When the Buddha had stayed at Vesālī for as long as he liked, he set out wandering toward the country of Bhaggā.*";
P_HTM[7177]="*Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena bhaggā tadavasari.**When he eventually arrived,*";
P_HTM[7178]="*Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā bhaggesu viharati susumāragire bhesakaḷāvane migadāye.**he stayed at Susumāragira in the Bhesakaḷā Grove, the deer park.*";
P_HTM[7179]="*Tena kho pana samayena bodhissa rājakumārassa kokanado nāma pāsādo acirakārito hoti, anajjhāvuttho samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā kenaci vā manussabhūtena.**At this time Prince Bodhi had recently built the Kokanada stilt house. It had not yet been inhabited by any monastic or brahmin, or anyone else.*";
P_HTM[7180]="*Atha kho bodhi rājakumāro sañcikāputtaṃ māṇavaṃ āmantesi—**The Prince said to the young brahmin Sañcikāputta,*";
P_HTM[7181]="*“ehi tvaṃ, samma sañcikāputta, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkama, upasaṅkamitvā mama vacanena bhagavato pāde sirasā vanda;**“My dear Sañcikāputta, please go to the Buddha, bow down in my name with your head at his feet,*";
P_HTM[7182]="*appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ puccha—**and ask*";
P_HTM[7183]="*‘bodhi, bhante, rājakumāro bhagavato pāde sirasā vandati, appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ pucchatī’ti.**if he is healthy, strong, and living at ease.*";
P_HTM[7184]="*Evañca vadehi—**And then say,*";
P_HTM[7185]="*‘adhivāsetu kira, bhante, bhagavā bodhissa rājakumārassa svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghenā’”ti.**‘Sir, please accept tomorrow’s meal, together with the Sangha of monks, from Prince Bodhi.’”*";
P_HTM[7186]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho sañcikāputto māṇavo bodhissa rājakumārassa paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi, sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Saying, “Yes, Sir,” Sañcikāputta went to the Buddha and exchanged pleasantries with him. He then sat down*";
P_HTM[7187]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho sañcikāputto māṇavo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and told the Buddha all he had been asked to say,*";
P_HTM[7188]="*“bodhi kho rājakumāro bhoto gotamassa pāde sirasā vandati, appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ pucchati.* **";
P_HTM[7189]="*Evañca vadeti—* **";
P_HTM[7190]="*‘adhivāsetu kira bhavaṃ gotamo bodhissa rājakumārassa svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghenā’”ti.**concluding with the invitation for the meal on the following day.*";
P_HTM[7191]="*Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena.**The Buddha consented by remaining silent.*";
P_HTM[7192]="*Atha kho sañcikāputto māṇavo bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā yena bodhi rājakumāro tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bodhiṃ rājakumāraṃ etadavoca—**Knowing that the Buddha had consented, Sañcikāputta got up from his seat, returned to the Prince, and told him what had happened.*";
P_HTM[7193]="*“avocumha kho mayaṃ bhoto vacanena taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ—* **";
P_HTM[7194]="*‘bodhi kho rājakumāro bhoto gotamassa pāde sirasā vandati, appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ pucchati.* **";
P_HTM[7195]="*Evañca vadeti—* **";
P_HTM[7196]="*adhivāsetu kira bhavaṃ gotamo bodhissa rājakumārassa svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghenā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7197]="*Adhivutthañca pana samaṇena gotamenā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7198]="*Atha kho bodhi rājakumāro tassā rattiyā accayena paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā, kokanadañca pāsādaṃ odātehi dussehi santharāpetvā yāva pacchimasopānakaḷevarā, sañcikāputtaṃ māṇavaṃ āmantesi—**The next morning Prince Bodhi had various kinds of fine food prepared, and had the entire Kokanada stilt house covered with white cloth, all the way to the bottom step of the staircase. He then said to Sañcikāputta,*";
P_HTM[7199]="*“ehi tvaṃ, samma sañcikāputta, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkama, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato kālaṃ ārocehi—**“Go to the Buddha*";
P_HTM[7200]="*‘kālo, bhante, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan’”ti.**and tell him the meal is ready.”*";
P_HTM[7201]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho sañcikāputto māṇavo bodhissa rājakumārassa paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato kālaṃ ārocesi—**He did as instructed.*";
P_HTM[7202]="*“kālo, bho gotama, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7203]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena bodhissa rājakumārassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami.**Soon afterwards, the Buddha robed up in the morning, took his bowl and robe, and went the Prince’s house.*";
P_HTM[7204]="*Tena kho pana samayena bodhi rājakumāro bahidvārakoṭṭhake ṭhito hoti, bhagavantaṃ āgamayamāno.**The Prince was standing outside the gateway, waiting for the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7205]="*Addasā kho bodhi rājakumāro bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**When he saw the Buddha coming,*";
P_HTM[7206]="*Disvāna tato paccuggantvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā purekkhatvā yena kokanado pāsādo tenupasaṅkami.**he went out to meet him, bowed down to him, and went to the Kokanada stilt house with the Buddha in front.*";
P_HTM[7207]="*Atha kho bhagavā pacchimasopānakaḷevaraṃ nissāya aṭṭhāsi.**But the Buddha stopped at the bottom stair of that staircase.*";
P_HTM[7208]="*Atha kho bodhi rājakumāro bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**The Prince said,*";
P_HTM[7209]="*“akkamatu, bhante, bhagavā dussāni, akkamatu sugato dussāni, yaṃ mama assa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti.**“Sir, please step on the cloth. It will be for my longterm benefit and happiness.”*";
P_HTM[7210]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā tuṇhī ahosi.**But the Buddha remained silent.*";
P_HTM[7211]="*Dutiyampi kho …pe…**A second time the Prince repeated his request, but the Buddha still remained silent.*";
P_HTM[7212]="*tatiyampi kho bodhi rājakumāro bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**When the Prince made his request for the third time,*";
P_HTM[7213]="*“akkamatu, bhante, bhagavā dussāni, akkamatu sugato dussāni, yaṃ mama assa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7214]="*Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ apalokesi.**the Buddha looked at Venerable Ānanda.*";
P_HTM[7215]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando bodhiṃ rājakumāraṃ etadavoca—**And Ānanda said to the Prince,*";
P_HTM[7216]="*“saṃharantu, rājakumāra, dussāni.**“Please fold up the cloth.*";
P_HTM[7217]="*Na bhagavā celapaṭikaṃ akkamissati pacchimaṃ janataṃ tathāgato anukampatī”ti.**The Buddha doesn’t step on cloth coverings. The Buddha has compassion for later generations.”*";
P_HTM[7218]="*Atha kho bodhi rājakumāro dussāni saṃharāpetvā uparikokanade pāsāde āsanaṃ paññapesi.**The Prince then had the cloth folded up and had a seat prepared up in the stilt house.*";
P_HTM[7219]="*Atha kho bhagavā kokanadaṃ pāsādaṃ abhiruhitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghena.**The Buddha ascended the house and sat down on the prepared seat together with the Sangha of monks.*";
P_HTM[7220]="*Atha kho bodhi rājakumāro buddhappamukhaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappetvā sampavāretvā, bhagavantaṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ, ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**The Prince personally served the various kinds of fine food to the Sangha of monks headed by the Buddha. When the Buddha had finished his meal and had washed his hands and bowl, the Prince sat down to one side.*";
P_HTM[7221]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho bodhiṃ rājakumāraṃ bhagavā dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi.**The Buddha instructed, inspired, and gladdened him with a teaching, after which he got up from his seat and left.*";
P_HTM[7222]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[7223]="*“na, bhikkhave, celapaṭikā akkamitabbā.**“You should not step on a cloth covering.*";
P_HTM[7224]="*Yo akkameyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7225]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā itthī apagatagabbhā bhikkhū nimantetvā dussaṃ paññapetvā etadavoca—**On one occasion a woman who was unable to conceive invited the monks, prepared a cloth, and said,*";
P_HTM[7226]="*“akkamatha, bhante, dussan”ti.**“Venerables, please step on the cloth.”*";
P_HTM[7227]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā na akkamanti.**But being afraid of wrongdoing, they refused.*";
P_HTM[7228]="*“Akkamatha, bhante, dussaṃ maṅgalatthāyā”ti.**“Please step on the cloth as a blessing.”*";
P_HTM[7229]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā na akkamiṃsu.**They still refused.*";
P_HTM[7230]="*Atha kho sā itthī ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**That woman complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7231]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā maṅgalatthāya yāciyamānā celapaṭikaṃ na akkamissantī”ti.**“How can the venerables, when asked, not step on a cloth as a blessing?”*";
P_HTM[7232]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassā itthiyā ujjhāyantiyā khiyyantiyā vipācentiyā.**The monks heard the complaints of that woman*";
P_HTM[7233]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**and they told the Buddha what had happened.*";
P_HTM[7234]="*“Gihī, bhikkhave, maṅgalikā.**“Householders want blessings.*";
P_HTM[7235]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gihīnaṃ maṅgalatthāya yāciyamānena celapaṭikaṃ akkamitun”ti.**I allow you, when asked, to step on a cloth covering as a blessing for householders.”*";
P_HTM[7236]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū dhotapādakaṃ akkamituṃ kukkuccāyanti.**Being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not step on a sheet after washing their feet.*";
P_HTM[7237]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7238]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, dhotapādakaṃ akkamitun”ti.**“I allow you to step on a sheet after washing your feet.”*";
P_HTM[7239]="*Dutiyabhāṇavāro niṭṭhito.**The second section for recitation is finished.*";
P_HTM[7240]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhaggesu yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena sāvatthi tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**When the Buddha had stayed in the country of Bhaggā for as long as he liked, he set out wandering toward Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[7241]="*Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena sāvatthi tadavasari.**When he eventually arrived,*";
P_HTM[7242]="*Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**he stayed in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[7243]="*Atha kho visākhā migāramātā ghaṭakañca katakañca sammajjaniñca ādāya yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Soon Visākhā Migāramātā went to the Buddha, taking a waterpot, a ceramic foot scrubber, and a broom. She bowed to the Buddha, sat down,*";
P_HTM[7244]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho visākhā migāramātā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[7245]="*“paṭiggaṇhātu me, bhante, bhagavā ghaṭakañca katakañca sammajjaniñca, yaṃ mama assa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti.**“Venerable Sir, for my longterm benefit and happiness, please accept this waterpot, this foot scrubber, and this broom.”*";
P_HTM[7246]="*Paṭiggahesi bhagavā ghaṭakañca sammajjaniñca.**The Buddha accepted the waterpot and the broom,*";
P_HTM[7247]="*Na bhagavā katakaṃ paṭiggahesi.**but not the ceramic foot scrubber.*";
P_HTM[7248]="*Atha kho bhagavā visākhaṃ migāramātaraṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi.**He then instructed, inspired, and gladdened her with a teaching,*";
P_HTM[7249]="*Atha kho visākhā migāramātā bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**after which she got up from her seat, bowed down, circumambulated him with her right side toward him, and left.*";
P_HTM[7250]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[7251]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ghaṭakañca sammajjaniñca.**“I allow waterpots and brooms.*";
P_HTM[7252]="*Na, bhikkhave, katakaṃ paribhuñjitabbaṃ.**But you should not use a ceramic foot scrubber.*";
P_HTM[7253]="*Yo paribhuñjeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7254]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tisso pādaghaṃsaniyo—**I allow three kinds of foot scrubbers:*";
P_HTM[7255]="*sakkharaṃ, kathalaṃ, samuddapheṇakan”ti.**stones, pebbles, and pumice.”*";
P_HTM[7256]="*Atha kho visākhā migāramātā vidhūpanañca tālavaṇṭañca ādāya yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Visākhā again went to the Buddha, now taking a fan and a palm-leaf fan. She bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[7257]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho visākhā migāramātā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[7258]="*“paṭiggaṇhātu me, bhante, bhagavā vidhūpanañca tālavaṇṭañca, yaṃ mama assa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti.**“Venerable Sir, for my longterm benefit and happiness, please accept this fan and this palm-leaf fan.”*";
P_HTM[7259]="*Paṭiggahesi bhagavā vidhūpanañca tālavaṇṭañca.**The Buddha accepted both.*";
P_HTM[7260]="*Atha kho bhagavā visākhaṃ migāramātaraṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi …pe…**He then instructed, inspired, and gladdened her with a teaching, after which she got up from her seat, bowed, circumambulated him with her right side toward him,*";
P_HTM[7261]="*padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**and left.*";
P_HTM[7262]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[7263]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, vidhūpanañca tālavaṇṭañcā”ti.**“I allow a fan and a palm-leaf fan.”*";
P_HTM[7264]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa makasabījanī uppannā hoti.**On one occasion the Sangha was given a mosquito whisk.*";
P_HTM[7265]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7266]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, makasabījanin”ti.**“I allow a mosquito whisk.”*";
P_HTM[7267]="*Cāmaribījanī uppannā hoti.**The Sangha was given a yak-tail whisk.*";
P_HTM[7268]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7269]="*“Na, bhikkhave, cāmaribījanī dhāretabbā.**“You should not use a yak-tail whisk.*";
P_HTM[7270]="*Yo dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7271]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tisso bījaniyo—**I allow three kinds of fans:*";
P_HTM[7272]="*vākamayaṃ, usīramayaṃ, morapiñchamayan”ti.**made of bark, made of khus grass, and made of peacocks’ tail feathers.”*";
P_HTM[7273]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa chattaṃ uppannaṃ hoti.**On one occasion the Sangha was given a sunshade.*";
P_HTM[7274]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7275]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, chattan”ti.**“I allow a sunshade.”*";
P_HTM[7276]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū chattappaggahitā āhiṇḍanti.**Soon afterwards the monks from the group of six walked about holding a sunshade.*";
P_HTM[7277]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro upāsako sambahulehi ājīvakasāvakehi saddhiṃ uyyānaṃ agamāsi.**When a certain Buddhist lay follower and a number of Ājīvaka followers went to a park,*";
P_HTM[7278]="*Addasāsuṃ kho te ājīvakasāvakā chabbaggiye bhikkhū dūratova chattappaggahite āgacchante.**they saw the group of six monks with their sunshades.*";
P_HTM[7279]="*Disvāna taṃ upāsakaṃ etadavocuṃ—**They said to that lay follower,*";
P_HTM[7280]="*“ete kho ayyā tumhākaṃ bhadantā chattappaggahitā āgacchanti, seyyathāpi gaṇakamahāmattā”ti.**“These venerables of yours are coming. They are holding sunshades, just like accountants and government officials.”*";
P_HTM[7281]="*“Nāyyā ete bhikkhū, paribbājakā”ti.**“These are not monks; they are wanderers.”*";
P_HTM[7282]="*“Bhikkhū na bhikkhū”ti abbhutaṃ akaṃsu.**And they made a bet on whether they were monks or not.*";
P_HTM[7283]="*Atha kho so upāsako upagate sañjānitvā ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**When the monks came close, that lay follower recognized them. And he complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7284]="*“kathañhi nāma bhadantā chattappaggahitā āhiṇḍissantī”ti.**“How can the venerables walk about holding sunshades?”*";
P_HTM[7285]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassa upāsakassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa.**The monks heard the complaints of that lay follower*";
P_HTM[7286]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**and they told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7287]="*“Saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave …pe…**“Is it true, monks, that the monks from the group of six are acting like this?”*";
P_HTM[7288]="*“saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[7289]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[7290]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[7291]="*“na, bhikkhave, chattaṃ dhāretabbaṃ.**“You should not use a sunshade.*";
P_HTM[7292]="*Yo dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7293]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu gilāno hoti.**Soon afterwards a certain sick monk*";
P_HTM[7294]="*Tassa bhikkhuno vinā chattaṃ na phāsu hoti.**was not comfortable without a sunshade.*";
P_HTM[7295]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7296]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānassa chattaṃ dhāretun”ti.**“I allow a sick monk to use a sunshade.”*";
P_HTM[7297]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū—**When they heard*";
P_HTM[7298]="*gilānasseva bhagavatā chattaṃ anuññātaṃ no agilānassāti—**that the Buddha had allowed sunshades for the sick, but not for the healthy,*";
P_HTM[7299]="*ārāme ārāmūpacāre chattaṃ dhāretuṃ kukkuccāyanti.**and being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not use sunshades in the monastery or in the vicinity of the monastery.*";
P_HTM[7300]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7301]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, agilānenapi ārāme ārāmūpacāre chattaṃ dhāretun”ti.**“I allow you to use a sunshade in a monastery and in the vicinity of a monastery, even if you’re healthy.”*";
P_HTM[7302]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu sikkāya pattaṃ uṭṭitvā daṇḍe ālaggetvā vikāle aññatarena gāmadvārena atikkamati.**On one occasion a monk put his almsbowl in a carrying net, hung it from a staff, and entered the gateway to a certain village at the wrong time.*";
P_HTM[7303]="*Manussā—**People said,*";
P_HTM[7304]="*“esayyo coro gacchati, asissa vijjotalatī”ti anupatitvā gahetvā sañjānitvā muñciṃsu.**“This must be a gangster coming with his gleaming sword.” They pounced and took hold of him, but when they recognized him, they let him go.*";
P_HTM[7305]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**He returned to the monastery and told the monks what had happened.*";
P_HTM[7306]="*“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, āvuso, daṇḍasikkaṃ dhāresī”ti?**They said, “So you used a carrying net and a staff?”*";
P_HTM[7307]="*“Evamāvuso”ti.**“Yes.”*";
P_HTM[7308]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[7309]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhu daṇḍasikkaṃ dhāressasī”ti.**“How can a monk use a carrying net and a staff?”*";
P_HTM[7310]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha …*";
P_HTM[7311]="*“saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[7312]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing him …*";
P_HTM[7313]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[7314]="*“na, bhikkhave, daṇḍasikkā dhāretabbā.**“You should not use a carrying net and a staff.*";
P_HTM[7315]="*Yo dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7316]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu gilāno hoti, na sakkoti vinā daṇḍena āhiṇḍituṃ.**On one occasion there was a sick monk who was unable to walk about without a staff.*";
P_HTM[7317]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7318]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānassa bhikkhuno daṇḍasammutiṃ dātuṃ.**“I allow you to give a sick monk permission to use a staff.*";
P_HTM[7319]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbā.**And it should be given like this.*";
P_HTM[7320]="*Tena gilānena bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**The sick monk should approach the Sangha, put his upper robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and say:*";
P_HTM[7321]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, gilāno;**‘Venerables, I’m sick.*";
P_HTM[7322]="*na sakkomi vinā daṇḍena āhiṇḍituṃ.**I’m unable to walk about without a staff.*";
P_HTM[7323]="*Sohaṃ, bhante, saṅghaṃ daṇḍasammutiṃ yācāmī’ti.**I ask the Sangha for permission to use a staff.’*";
P_HTM[7324]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbā.**And he should ask a second*";
P_HTM[7325]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[7326]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[7327]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[7328]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu gilāno, na sakkoti vinā daṇḍena āhiṇḍituṃ.**Monk so-and-so is sick. He is unable to walk about without a staff.*";
P_HTM[7329]="*So saṅghaṃ daṇḍasammutiṃ yācati.**He is asking the Sangha for permission to use a staff.*";
P_HTM[7330]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno daṇḍasammutiṃ dadeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, it should give him permission to use a staff.*";
P_HTM[7331]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[7332]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[7333]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu gilāno, na sakkoti vinā daṇḍena āhiṇḍituṃ.**Monk so-and-so is sick. He is unable to walk about without a staff.*";
P_HTM[7334]="*So saṅghaṃ daṇḍasammutiṃ yācati.**He is asking the Sangha for permission to use a staff.*";
P_HTM[7335]="*Saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno daṇḍasammutiṃ deti.**The Sangha gives him permission to use a staff.*";
P_HTM[7336]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno daṇḍasammutiyā dānaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of giving monk so-and-so permission to use a staff should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[7337]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[7338]="*Dinnā saṅghena itthannāmassa bhikkhuno daṇḍasammuti.**The Sangha has given monk so-and-so permission to use a staff.*";
P_HTM[7339]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[7340]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu gilāno hoti, na sakkoti vinā sikkāya pattaṃ pariharituṃ.**On one occasion there was a sick monk who was unable to carry his almsbowl around without a carrying-net.*";
P_HTM[7341]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7342]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānassa bhikkhuno sikkāsammutiṃ dātuṃ.**“I allow you to give a sick monk permission to use a a carrying-net.*";
P_HTM[7343]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbā.**And it should be given like this.*";
P_HTM[7344]="*Tena gilānena bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**The sick monk should approach the Sangha, put his upper robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and say:*";
P_HTM[7345]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, gilāno;**‘Venerables, I’m sick.*";
P_HTM[7346]="*na sakkomi vinā sikkāya pattaṃ pariharituṃ.**I’m unable to carry my bowl around without a carrying-net.*";
P_HTM[7347]="*Sohaṃ, bhante, saṅghaṃ sikkāsammutiṃ yācāmī’ti.**I ask the Sangha for permission to use a carrying-net.’*";
P_HTM[7348]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbā.**And he should ask a second*";
P_HTM[7349]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[7350]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[7351]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[7352]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu gilāno, na sakkoti vinā sikkāya pattaṃ pariharituṃ.**Monk so-and-so is sick. He is unable to carry his bowl around without a carrying-net.*";
P_HTM[7353]="*So saṅghaṃ sikkāsammutiṃ yācati.**He is asking the Sangha for permission to use a carrying-net.*";
P_HTM[7354]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno sikkāsammutiṃ dadeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, it should give him permission to use a carrying-net.*";
P_HTM[7355]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[7356]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[7357]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu gilāno, na sakkoti vinā sikkāya pattaṃ pariharituṃ.**Monk so-and-so is sick. He is unable to carry his bowl around without a carrying-net.*";
P_HTM[7358]="*So saṅghaṃ sikkāsammutiṃ yācati.**He is asking the Sangha for permission to use a carrying-net.*";
P_HTM[7359]="*Saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno sikkāsammutiṃ deti.**The Sangha gives him permission to use a carrying-net.*";
P_HTM[7360]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno sikkāsammutiyā dānaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of giving monk so-and-so permission to use a carrying-net should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[7361]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[7362]="*Dinnā saṅghena itthannāmassa bhikkhuno sikkāsammuti.**The Sangha has given monk so-and-so permission to use a carrying-net.*";
P_HTM[7363]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[7364]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu gilāno hoti, na sakkoti vinā daṇḍena āhiṇḍituṃ, na sakkoti vinā sikkāya pattaṃ pariharituṃ.**On one occasion there was a sick monk who was unable to walk about without a staff or to carry his almsbowl around without a carrying-net.*";
P_HTM[7365]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7366]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānassa bhikkhuno daṇḍasikkāsammutiṃ dātuṃ.**“I allow you to give a sick monk permission to use a staff and a carrying-net.*";
P_HTM[7367]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbā.**And it should be given like this.*";
P_HTM[7368]="*Tena gilānena bhikkhunā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**The sick monk should approach the Sangha, put his upper robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, raise his joined palms, and say:*";
P_HTM[7369]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, gilāno;**‘Venerables, I’m sick.*";
P_HTM[7370]="*na sakkomi vinā daṇḍena āhiṇḍituṃ;**I’m unable to walk about without a staff*";
P_HTM[7371]="*na sakkomi vinā sikkāya pattaṃ pariharituṃ.**or to carry my bowl around without a carrying-net.*";
P_HTM[7372]="*Sohaṃ, bhante, saṅghaṃ daṇḍasikkāsammutiṃ yācāmī’ti.**I ask the Sangha to give me permission to use a staff and a carrying-net.’*";
P_HTM[7373]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbā.**And he should ask a second*";
P_HTM[7374]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[7375]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[7376]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[7377]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu gilāno, na sakkoti vinā daṇḍena āhiṇḍituṃ, na sakkoti vinā sikkāya pattaṃ pariharituṃ.**Monk so-and-so is sick. He is unable to walk about without a staff or to carry his bowl around without a carrying-net.*";
P_HTM[7378]="*So saṅghaṃ daṇḍasikkāsammutiṃ yācati.**He is asking the Sangha for permission to use a staff and a carrying-net.*";
P_HTM[7379]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno daṇḍasikkāsammutiṃ dadeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, it should give him permission to use a staff and a carrying-net.*";
P_HTM[7380]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[7381]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[7382]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu gilāno na sakkoti vinā daṇḍena āhiṇḍituṃ, na sakkoti vinā sikkāya pattaṃ pariharituṃ.**Monk so-and-so is sick. He is unable to walk about without a staff or to carry his bowl around without a carrying-net.*";
P_HTM[7383]="*So saṅghaṃ daṇḍasikkāsammutiṃ yācati.**He is asking the Sangha for permission to use a staff and a carrying-net.*";
P_HTM[7384]="*Saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno daṇḍasikkāsammutiṃ deti.**The Sangha gives him permission to use a staff and a carrying-net.*";
P_HTM[7385]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno daṇḍasikkāsammutiyā dānaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of giving monk so-and-so permission to use a staff and a carrying-net should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[7386]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[7387]="*Dinnā saṅghena itthannāmassa bhikkhuno daṇḍasikkāsammuti.**The Sangha has given monk so-and-so permission to use a staff and a carrying-net.*";
P_HTM[7388]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[7389]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu romanthako hoti.**At that time there was a monk who was a regurgitator.*";
P_HTM[7390]="*So romanthitvā romanthitvā ajjhoharati.**After regurgitating, he would swallow.*";
P_HTM[7391]="*Bhikkhū ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[7392]="*“vikālāyaṃ bhikkhu bhojanaṃ bhuñjatī”ti.**“This monk is eating at the wrong time.”*";
P_HTM[7393]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7394]="*“Eso, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aciraṅgoyoniyā cuto.**“This monk has only recently passed away as a cow.*";
P_HTM[7395]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, romanthakassa romanthanaṃ.**I allow a regurgitator to regurgitate.*";
P_HTM[7396]="*Na ca, bhikkhave, bahimukhadvāraṃ nīharitvā ajjhoharitabbaṃ.**But you should not take it out of the mouth and then swallow it.*";
P_HTM[7397]="*Yo ajjhohareyya, yathādhammo kāretabbo”ti.**If you do, you should be dealt with according to the rule.”*";
P_HTM[7398]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa pūgassa saṅghabhattaṃ hoti.**Soon afterwards a certain association was offering a meal to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[7399]="*Bhattagge bahusitthāni pakiriyiṃsu.**Lots of rice fell on the floor in the dining hall.*";
P_HTM[7400]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7401]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā odane diyyamāne na sakkaccaṃ paṭiggahessanti, ekamekaṃ sitthaṃ kammasatena niṭṭhāyatī”ti.**“When they are given rice, how can the Sakyan monastics not receive it with care? Each lump of rice is the result of a lot of work.”*";
P_HTM[7402]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people.*";
P_HTM[7403]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7404]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, yaṃ diyyamānaṃ patati, taṃ sāmaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjituṃ.**“I allow you to pick up yourselves what falls down when given, and then eat it.*";
P_HTM[7405]="*Pariccattaṃ taṃ, bhikkhave, dāyakehī”ti.**It has been relinquished by the donors.”*";
P_HTM[7406]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu dīghehi nakhehi piṇḍāya carati.**On one occasion a certain monk with long nails was walking for alms.*";
P_HTM[7407]="*Aññatarā itthī passitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—**A woman who saw him said to him,*";
P_HTM[7408]="*“ehi, bhante, methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevā”ti.**“Come, Venerable, and have sex.”*";
P_HTM[7409]="*“Alaṃ, bhagini, netaṃ kappatī”ti.**“It’s not allowable.”*";
P_HTM[7410]="*“Sace kho tvaṃ, bhante, nappaṭisevissasi, idānāhaṃ attano nakhehi gattāni vilikhitvā kuppaṃ karissāmi—**“If you don’t, I’ll scratch my limbs with my nails and make a scene,*";
P_HTM[7411]="*ayaṃ maṃ bhikkhu vippakarotī”ti.**saying that you abused me.”*";
P_HTM[7412]="*“Pajānāhi tvaṃ, bhaginī”ti.**“That’s your business, sister.”*";
P_HTM[7413]="*Atha kho sā itthī attano nakhehi gattāni vilikhitvā kuppaṃ akāsi—**Yet that woman did what she had threatened to do.*";
P_HTM[7414]="*“ayaṃ maṃ bhikkhu vippakarotī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7415]="*Manussā upadhāvitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ aggahesuṃ.**People came running to and took hold of that monk.*";
P_HTM[7416]="*Addasāsuṃ kho te manussā tassā itthiyā nakhe chavimpi lohitampi.**But when they saw the skin and blood on that woman’s nails,*";
P_HTM[7417]="*Disvāna—**they realized*";
P_HTM[7418]="*“imissāyeva itthiyā idaṃ kammaṃ, akārako bhikkhū”ti—**she had done it herself,*";
P_HTM[7419]="*taṃ bhikkhuṃ muñciṃsu.**and they released the monk.*";
P_HTM[7420]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**That monk then returned to the monastery and told the monks what had happened. They said,*";
P_HTM[7421]="*“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, āvuso, dīghe nakhe dhāresī”ti?**“So you grow your nails long?”*";
P_HTM[7422]="*“Evamāvuso”ti.**“Yes.”*";
P_HTM[7423]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[7424]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhu dīghe nakhe dhāressasī”ti.**“How can a monk grow his nails long?”*";
P_HTM[7425]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7426]="*“Na, bhikkhave, dīghā nakhā dhāretabbā.**“You should not grow your nails long.*";
P_HTM[7427]="*Yo dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7428]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū nakhenapi nakhaṃ chindanti, mukhenapi nakhaṃ chindanti, kuṭṭepi ghaṃsanti.**Soon afterwards the monks were cutting their nails with their nails, with their teeth, or by grinding them on a wall.*";
P_HTM[7429]="*Aṅguliyo dukkhā honti.**Their fingers hurt.*";
P_HTM[7430]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7431]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, nakhacchedanan”ti.**“I allow nail clippers.”*";
P_HTM[7432]="*Salohitaṃ nakhaṃ chindanti.**They cut their nails so short that they bled.*";
P_HTM[7433]="*Aṅguliyo dukkhā honti …pe…**Their fingers hurt.*";
P_HTM[7434]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, maṃsappamāṇena nakhaṃ chinditun”ti.**“I allow you to cut your nails so that they are even with the tip of the flesh.”*";
P_HTM[7435]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū vīsatimaṭṭhaṃ kārāpenti.**At this time the monks from the group of six polished their finger and toe nails.*";
P_HTM[7436]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7437]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[7438]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7439]="*“Na, bhikkhave, vīsatimaṭṭhaṃ kārāpetabbaṃ.**“You should not polish your finger and toe nails.*";
P_HTM[7440]="*Yo kārāpeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7441]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, malamattaṃ apakaḍḍhitun”ti.**But I allow you to remove dirt.”*";
P_HTM[7442]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhūnaṃ kesā dīghā honti.**At that time the monks had long hair.*";
P_HTM[7443]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7444]="*“Ussahanti pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhū aññamaññaṃ kese oropetun”ti?**“Are you able to shave each other’s heads?”*";
P_HTM[7445]="*“Ussahanti, bhagavā”ti.**“We are.”*";
P_HTM[7446]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā …pe…**The Buddha then gave a teaching*";
P_HTM[7447]="*bhikkhū āmantesi—**and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[7448]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, khuraṃ khurasilaṃ khurasipāṭikaṃ namatakaṃ sabbaṃ khurabhaṇḍan”ti.**“I allow a razor, a whetstone, a razor case, felt, and all barber equipment.”*";
P_HTM[7449]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū massuṃ kappāpenti …pe…**At this time the monks from the group of six trimmed their beards,*";
P_HTM[7450]="*massuṃ vaḍḍhāpenti …**grew their beards long,*";
P_HTM[7451]="*golomikaṃ kārāpenti …**grew goatees,*";
P_HTM[7452]="*caturassakaṃ kārāpenti …**grew sideburns,*";
P_HTM[7453]="*parimukhaṃ kārāpenti …**removed their chest hair,*";
P_HTM[7454]="*aḍḍhadukaṃ kārāpenti …**sculpted their stomach hair,*";
P_HTM[7455]="*dāṭhikaṃ ṭhapenti …**grew mustaches,*";
P_HTM[7456]="*sambādhe lomaṃ saṃharāpenti.**and removed the hair from their private parts.*";
P_HTM[7457]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7458]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[7459]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7460]="*“Na, bhikkhave, massu kappāpetabbaṃ …pe…**“You should not trim your beard,*";
P_HTM[7461]="*na massu vaḍḍhāpetabbaṃ …**grow your beard long,*";
P_HTM[7462]="*na golomikaṃ kārāpetabbaṃ …**grow a goatee,*";
P_HTM[7463]="*na caturassakaṃ kārāpetabbaṃ …**grow sideburns,*";
P_HTM[7464]="*na parimukhaṃ kārāpetabbaṃ …**remove your chest hair,*";
P_HTM[7465]="*na aḍḍhadukaṃ kārāpetabbaṃ …**sculpt your stomach hair,*";
P_HTM[7466]="*na dāṭhikā ṭhapetabbā …**grow a mustache,*";
P_HTM[7467]="*na sambādhe lomaṃ saṃharāpetabbaṃ.**or remove the hair from your private parts.*";
P_HTM[7468]="*Yo saṃharāpeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7469]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa bhikkhuno sambādhe vaṇo hoti.**A certain monk had a sore on his private parts,*";
P_HTM[7470]="*Bhesajjaṃ na santiṭṭhati.**and the medicine did not stick.*";
P_HTM[7471]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7472]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ābādhappaccayā sambādhe lomaṃ saṃharāpetun”ti.**“I allow you to remove hair on the private parts if you have a disease.”*";
P_HTM[7473]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kattarikāya kese chedāpenti.**At that time the monks from the group of six cut their hair with scissors.*";
P_HTM[7474]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7475]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[7476]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7477]="*“Na, bhikkhave, kattarikāya kesā chedāpetabbā.**“You should not cut your hair with scissors.*";
P_HTM[7478]="*Yo chedāpeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7479]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa bhikkhuno sīse vaṇo hoti, na sakkoti khurena kese oropetuṃ.**A monk who had a sore on his head was unable to shave with a razor.*";
P_HTM[7480]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7481]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ābādhappaccayā kattarikāya kese chedāpetun”ti.**“I allow you to cut your hair with scissors if you have a disease.”*";
P_HTM[7482]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū dīghāni nāsikālomāni dhārenti.**At this time the monks grew their nasal hair long.*";
P_HTM[7483]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7484]="*“seyyathāpi pisācillikā”ti.**“They are just like goblins.”*";
P_HTM[7485]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7486]="*“Na, bhikkhave, dīghaṃ nāsikālomaṃ dhāretabbaṃ.**“You should not grow your nasal hair long.*";
P_HTM[7487]="*Yo dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7488]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū sakkharikāyapi madhusitthakenapi nāsikālomaṃ gāhāpenti.**The monks had their nasal hair removed with small stones or beeswax.*";
P_HTM[7489]="*Nāsikā dukkhā honti.**Their noses hurt.*";
P_HTM[7490]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7491]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, saṇḍāsan”ti.**“I allow tweezers.”*";
P_HTM[7492]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū palitaṃ gāhāpenti.**The monks from the group of six had their gray hairs removed.*";
P_HTM[7493]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7494]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[7495]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7496]="*“Na, bhikkhave, palitaṃ gāhāpetabbaṃ.**“You should not remove gray hairs.*";
P_HTM[7497]="*Yo gāhāpeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7498]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa bhikkhuno kaṇṇagūthakehi kaṇṇā thakitā honti.**On one occasion a monk’s ear was blocked by earwax.*";
P_HTM[7499]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7500]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kaṇṇamalaharaṇin”ti.**“I allow an ear-pick.”*";
P_HTM[7501]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū uccāvacā kaṇṇamalaharaṇiyo dhārenti sovaṇṇamayaṃ rūpiyamayaṃ.**Soon the monks from the group of six used luxurious ear-picks made of gold and silver.*";
P_HTM[7502]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7503]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[7504]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7505]="*“Na, bhikkhave, uccāvacā kaṇṇamalaharaṇiyo dhāretabbā.**“You should not use a luxurious ear-pick.*";
P_HTM[7506]="*Yo dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassāti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7507]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, aṭṭhimayaṃ dantamayaṃ visāṇamayaṃ naḷamayaṃ veḷumayaṃ kaṭṭhamayaṃ jatumayaṃ phalamayaṃ lohamayaṃ saṅkhanābhimayan”ti.**I allow an ear-pick made of bone, ivory, horn, reed, bamboo, wood, resin, fruit, metal, or shell.”*";
P_HTM[7508]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bahuṃ lohabhaṇḍaṃ kaṃsabhaṇḍaṃ sannicayaṃ karonti.**At one time the monks from the group of six had amassed a large number of metal and bronze goods.*";
P_HTM[7509]="*Manussā vihāracārikaṃ āhiṇḍantā passitvā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People who were walking about the dwellings saw this, and they complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7510]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā bahuṃ lohabhaṇḍaṃ kaṃsabhaṇḍaṃ sannicayaṃ karissanti, seyyathāpi kaṃsapattharikā”ti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics amass a large number of metal and bronze goods? They are just like merchants.”*";
P_HTM[7511]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7512]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bahuṃ lohabhaṇḍaṃ kaṃsabhaṇḍaṃ sannicayo kātabbo.**“You should not amass a large number of metal and bronze goods.*";
P_HTM[7513]="*Yo kareyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7514]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū añjanimpi añjanisalākampi kaṇṇamalaharaṇimpi bandhanamattampi kukkuccāyanti.**Being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not accept ointment boxes, ointment sticks, earpicks, or even metal used for joining.*";
P_HTM[7515]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7516]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, añjaniṃ añjanisalākaṃ kaṇṇamalaharaṇiṃ bandhanamattan”ti.**“I allow an ointment box, an ointment stick, an ear-pick, and metal used for joining.”*";
P_HTM[7517]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū saṅghāṭipallatthikāya nisīdanti.**On one occasion the monks from the group of six were sitting using their upper robes as a back-and-knee strap.*";
P_HTM[7518]="*Saṅghāṭiyā pattā lujjanti.**The panels of the robes broke up.*";
P_HTM[7519]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7520]="*“Na, bhikkhave, saṅghāṭipallatthikāya nisīditabbaṃ.**“You should not sit using your upper robe as a back-and-knee strap.*";
P_HTM[7521]="*Yo nisīdeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7522]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu gilāno hoti.**A monk who was sick*";
P_HTM[7523]="*Tassa vinā āyogena na phāsu hoti.**was not comfortable without a back-and-knee strap.*";
P_HTM[7524]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7525]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, āyogan”ti.**“I allow a back-and-knee strap.”*";
P_HTM[7526]="*Atha kho bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The monks thought,*";
P_HTM[7527]="*“kathaṃ nu kho āyogo kātabbo”ti?**“How should we make back-and-knee straps?”*";
P_HTM[7528]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7529]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tantakaṃ vemaṃ kavaṭaṃ salākaṃ sabbaṃ tantabhaṇḍakan”ti.**“I allow a warp, a reed, a weft, a shuttle, and all weaving equipment.”*";
P_HTM[7530]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu akāyabandhano gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**On one occasion a monk entered a village for alms without a belt.*";
P_HTM[7531]="*Tassa rathikāya antaravāsako pabhassittha.**His sarong fell off on the street.*";
P_HTM[7532]="*Manussā ukkuṭṭhimakaṃsu.**People shouted out,*";
P_HTM[7533]="*So bhikkhu maṅku ahosi.**and he felt humiliated.*";
P_HTM[7534]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**When he had returned to the monastery, he told the monks what had happened.*";
P_HTM[7535]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They in turn told the Buddha, who said,*";
P_HTM[7536]="*“Na, bhikkhave, akāyabandhanena gāmo pavisitabbo.**“You should not enter a village without a belt.*";
P_HTM[7537]="*Yo paviseyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7538]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kāyabandhanan”ti.**I allow a belt.”*";
P_HTM[7539]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū uccāvacāni kāyabandhanāni dhārenti—**Soon the monks from the group of six wore luxurious belts:*";
P_HTM[7540]="*kalābukaṃ, deḍḍubhakaṃ, murajaṃ, maddavīṇaṃ.**belts with multiple strings, belts like the head of a water snake, belts of twisted strings of various colors, belts like ornamental strings.*";
P_HTM[7541]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7542]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[7543]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7544]="*“Na, bhikkhave, uccāvacāni kāyabandhanāni dhāretabbāni—**“You should not wear a luxurious belt.*";
P_HTM[7545]="*kalābukaṃ, deḍḍubhakaṃ, murajaṃ, maddavīṇaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7546]="*Yo dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7547]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, dve kāyabandhanāni—**I allow two kinds of belts:*";
P_HTM[7548]="*paṭṭikaṃ, sūkarantakan”ti.**made from strips of cloth and made from pigs’ intestines.”*";
P_HTM[7549]="*Kāyabandhanassa dasā jīranti …pe…**The edges of the belts wore away.*";
P_HTM[7550]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, murajaṃ maddavīṇan”ti.**“I allow a belt of twisted strings of various colors and a belt like ornamental strings.”*";
P_HTM[7551]="*Kāyabandhanassa anto jīrati …pe…**The ends of the belts wore away.*";
P_HTM[7552]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, sobhaṇaṃ guṇakan”ti.**“I allow looping the end and then sewing around the loop, and sewing into a knot.”*";
P_HTM[7553]="*Kāyabandhanassa pavananto jīrati …pe…**The loop at the end wore away.*";
P_HTM[7554]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, vidhan”ti.**“I allow a buckle.”*";
P_HTM[7555]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū uccāvace vidhe dhārenti sovaṇṇamayaṃ rūpiyamayaṃ.**Soon the monks from the group of six wore luxurious buckles made of gold and silver.*";
P_HTM[7556]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7557]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[7558]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7559]="*“Na, bhikkhave, uccāvacā vidhā dhāretabbā.**“You should not wear a luxurious buckle.*";
P_HTM[7560]="*Yo dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7561]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, aṭṭhimayaṃ …pe…**I allow a buckle made of bone, ivory, horn, reed, bamboo, wood, resin, fruit, metal,*";
P_HTM[7562]="*saṅkhanābhimayaṃ suttamayan”ti.**shell, and string.”*";
P_HTM[7563]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā ānando lahukā saṅghāṭiyo pārupitvā gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**On one occasion Venerable Ānanda robed up in light upper robes and entered a village for alms.*";
P_HTM[7564]="*Vātamaṇḍalikāya saṅghāṭiyo ukkhipiyiṃsu.**A whirlwind lifted up his robes.*";
P_HTM[7565]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**When he had returned to the monastery, he told the monks what had happened.*";
P_HTM[7566]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They in turn told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7567]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gaṇṭhikaṃ pāsakan”ti.**“I allow toggles and loops.”*";
P_HTM[7568]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū uccāvacā gaṇṭhikāyo dhārenti sovaṇṇamayaṃ rūpiyamayaṃ.**Soon the monks from the group of six wore luxurious toggles made of gold and silver.*";
P_HTM[7569]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7570]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[7571]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7572]="*“Na, bhikkhave, uccāvacā gaṇṭhikā dhāretabbā.**“You should not wear luxurious toggles.*";
P_HTM[7573]="*Yo dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7574]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, aṭṭhimayaṃ dantamayaṃ visāṇamayaṃ naḷamayaṃ veḷumayaṃ kaṭṭhamayaṃ jatumayaṃ phalamayaṃ lohamayaṃ saṅkhanābhimayaṃ suttamayan”ti.**I allow toggles made of bone, ivory, horn, reed, bamboo, wood, resin, fruit, metal, shell, and string.”*";
P_HTM[7575]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū gaṇṭhikampi pāsakampi cīvare appenti.**The monks fastened toggles and loops to their robes,*";
P_HTM[7576]="*Cīvaraṃ jīrati.**but it caused the robes to wear.*";
P_HTM[7577]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7578]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gaṇṭhikaphalakaṃ pāsakaphalakan”ti.**“I allow a toggle-shield and a loop-shield.”*";
P_HTM[7579]="*Gaṇṭhikaphalakampi pāsakaphalakampi ante appenti.**They fastened the toggle-shield and the loop-shield on the edge of the robe.*";
P_HTM[7580]="*Koṭṭo vivariyati.**The border of the robe opened up.*";
P_HTM[7581]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7582]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gaṇṭhikaphalakaṃ ante appetuṃ;**“I allow you to fasten the toggle-shield at the edge*";
P_HTM[7583]="*pāsakaphalakaṃ sattaṅgulaṃ vā aṭṭhaṅgulaṃ vā ogāhetvā appetun”ti.**and the loop-shield twelve or thirteen centimeters in from the edge.”*";
P_HTM[7584]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū gihinivatthaṃ nivāsenti—**At this time the monks from the group of six wore their sarongs like householders—*";
P_HTM[7585]="*hatthisoṇḍakaṃ, macchavāḷakaṃ, catukaṇṇakaṃ, tālavaṇṭakaṃ, satavalikaṃ.**in the elephant-trunk style, the fish-tail style, the four corner style, the palm-leaf style, and the hundred fold style.*";
P_HTM[7586]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7587]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[7588]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7589]="*“Na, bhikkhave, gihinivatthaṃ nivāsetabbaṃ—**“You should not wear your sarong like householders—*";
P_HTM[7590]="*hatthisoṇḍakaṃ, macchavāḷakaṃ, catukaṇṇakaṃ, tālavaṇṭakaṃ, satavalikaṃ.**in the elephant-trunk style, the fish-tail style, the four corner style, the palm-leaf style, and the hundred fold style.*";
P_HTM[7591]="*Yo nivāseyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7592]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū gihipārutaṃ pārupanti.**The monks from the group of six wore their upper robes like householders.*";
P_HTM[7593]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7594]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[7595]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7596]="*“Na, bhikkhave, gihipārutaṃ pārupitabbaṃ.**“You should not wear your upper robe like householders.*";
P_HTM[7597]="*Yo pārupeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7598]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū saṃvelliyaṃ nivāsenti.**The monks from the group of six wore their sarongs like loin cloths.*";
P_HTM[7599]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7600]="*“seyyathāpi rañño muṇḍavaṭṭī”ti.**“They are just like the king’s porters.”*";
P_HTM[7601]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7602]="*“Na, bhikkhave, saṃvelliyaṃ nivāsetabbaṃ.**“You should not wear your sarong like a loin cloth.*";
P_HTM[7603]="*Yo nivāseyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7604]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū ubhatokājaṃ haranti.**At that time the monks from the group of six used carrying poles with loads on both ends.*";
P_HTM[7605]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7606]="*“seyyathāpi rañño muṇḍavaṭṭī”ti.**“They are just like the king’s porters.”*";
P_HTM[7607]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7608]="*“Na, bhikkhave, ubhatokājaṃ haritabbaṃ.**“You should not use a carrying pole with loads on both ends.*";
P_HTM[7609]="*Yo hareyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7610]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ekatokājaṃ antarākājaṃ sīsabhāraṃ khandhabhāraṃ kaṭibhāraṃ olambakan”ti.**I allow a carrying pole with a load on one end, a two-person carrying pole with a load in the middle, loads for the head, loads for the shoulder, loads for the hip, and hanging loads.”*";
P_HTM[7611]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū dantakaṭṭhaṃ na khādanti.**At that time the monks did not clean their teeth.*";
P_HTM[7612]="*Mukhaṃ duggandhaṃ hoti.**As a consequence, they had bad breath.*";
P_HTM[7613]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7614]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā dantakaṭṭhassa akhādane.**“There are these five disadvantages of not cleaning your teeth:*";
P_HTM[7615]="*Acakkhussaṃ, mukhaṃ duggandhaṃ hoti, rasaharaṇiyo na visujjhanti, pittaṃ semhaṃ bhattaṃ pariyonandhati, bhattamassa nacchādeti—**it’s bad for your eyes; you get bad breath; your ability to taste is reduced; bile and phlegm cover over the food; you don’t enjoy the food.*";
P_HTM[7616]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā dantakaṭṭhassa akhādane.* **";
P_HTM[7617]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā dantakaṭṭhassa khādane.**There are these five benefits of cleaning your teeth:*";
P_HTM[7618]="*Cakkhussaṃ, mukhaṃ na duggandhaṃ hoti, rasaharaṇiyo visujjhanti, pittaṃ semhaṃ bhattaṃ na pariyonandhati, bhattamassa chādeti—**it’s good for your eyes; you don’t get bad breath; your ability to taste is improved; bile and phlegm don’t cover over the food; you enjoy the food.*";
P_HTM[7619]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā dantakaṭṭhassa khādane.* **";
P_HTM[7620]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, dantakaṭṭhan”ti.**I allow tooth cleaners.”*";
P_HTM[7621]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū dīghāni dantakaṭṭhāni khādanti, teheva sāmaṇeraṃ ākoṭenti.**The monks from the group of six used long tooth cleaners and even used them to hit the novice monks.*";
P_HTM[7622]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7623]="*“Na, bhikkhave, dīghaṃ dantakaṭṭhaṃ khāditabbaṃ.**“You should not use long tooth cleaners.*";
P_HTM[7624]="*Yo khādeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7625]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, aṭṭhaṅgulaparamaṃ dantakaṭṭhaṃ, na ca tena sāmaṇero ākoṭetabbo.**I allow tooth cleaners that are a maximum of thirteen centimeters long. And you should not use them to hit the novice monks.*";
P_HTM[7626]="*Yo ākoṭeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7627]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa bhikkhuno atimaṭāhakaṃ dantakaṭṭhaṃ khādantassa kaṇṭhe vilaggaṃ hoti.**On one occasion a monk used a tooth cleaner that was too short and it got stuck in his throat.*";
P_HTM[7628]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7629]="*“Na, bhikkhave, atimaṭāhakaṃ dantakaṭṭhaṃ khāditabbaṃ.**“You should not use tooth cleaners that are too short.*";
P_HTM[7630]="*Yo khādeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7631]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, caturaṅgulapacchimaṃ dantakaṭṭhan”ti.**You should not use tooth cleaners shorter than seven centimeters.”*";
P_HTM[7632]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū dāyaṃ ālimpenti.**On one occasion the monks from the group of six set fire to a grove.*";
P_HTM[7633]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7634]="*“seyyathāpi davaḍāhakā”ti.**“They are just like land clearers.”*";
P_HTM[7635]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7636]="*“Na, bhikkhave, dāyo ālimpitabbo.**“You should not set fire to groves.*";
P_HTM[7637]="*Yo ālimpeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7638]="*Tena kho pana samayena vihārā tiṇagahanā honti, davaḍāhe ḍayhamāne vihārā ḍayhanti.**On one occasion the dwellings were overgrown with grass. When the forest was burning, the dwellings burnt too.*";
P_HTM[7639]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyanti paṭaggiṃ dātuṃ, parittaṃ kātuṃ.**Being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not light a counter-fire for protection.*";
P_HTM[7640]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7641]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, davaḍāhe ḍayhamāne paṭaggiṃ dātuṃ, parittaṃ kātun”ti.**“When the forest is burning, I allow you to light a counter-fire for protection.”*";
P_HTM[7642]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū rukkhaṃ abhiruhanti, rukkhā rukkhaṃ saṅkamanti.**At that time the monks from the group of six ascended trees and then climbed from tree to tree.*";
P_HTM[7643]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7644]="*“seyyathāpi makkaṭā”ti.**“They are just like monkeys.”*";
P_HTM[7645]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7646]="*“Na, bhikkhave, rukkho abhiruhitabbo.**“You should not climb trees.*";
P_HTM[7647]="*Yo abhiruheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7648]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa bhikkhuno kosalesu janapade sāvatthiṃ gacchantassa antarāmagge hatthī pariyuṭṭhāti.**On one occasion a certain monk was walking on a road through the Kosalan country on his way to Sāvatthī when he was blocked by an elephant.*";
P_HTM[7649]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu rukkhamūlaṃ upadhāvitvā kukkuccāyanto rukkhaṃ na abhiruhi.**He quickly went up to a tree, but being afraid of wrongdoing, he did not climb it.*";
P_HTM[7650]="*So hatthī aññena agamāsi.**Soon the elephant went away.*";
P_HTM[7651]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu sāvatthiṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**When he arrived at Sāvatthī, he told the monks what had happened.*";
P_HTM[7652]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They in turn told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7653]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, sati karaṇīye porisaṃ rukkhaṃ abhiruhituṃ āpadāsu yāvadatthan”ti.**“When there is something to be done, I allow you to climb a tree to the height of a man, or as far as you need if there are dangers.”*";
P_HTM[7654]="*Tena kho pana samayena yameḷakekuṭā nāma bhikkhū dve bhātikā honti brāhmaṇajātikā kalyāṇavācā kalyāṇavākkaraṇā.**At this time there were two monks called Yameḷa and Kekuṭa, brothers born into a brahmin family, who were well-spoken and had good voices.*";
P_HTM[7655]="*Te yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu.**They went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[7656]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ—**and said,*";
P_HTM[7657]="*“etarahi, bhante, bhikkhū nānānāmā nānāgottā nānājaccā nānākulā pabbajitā.**“Venerable Sir, the monks now have a variety of names, and come from a variety of families, castes, and households.*";
P_HTM[7658]="*Te sakāya niruttiyā buddhavacanaṃ dūsenti.**They corrupt the word of the Buddha by using their own expressions.*";
P_HTM[7659]="*Handa mayaṃ, bhante, buddhavacanaṃ chandaso āropemā”ti.**Now we could give metrical form to the word of the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[7660]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them,*";
P_HTM[7661]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, evaṃ vakkhatha—**“Foolish men, how can you say such a thing?*";
P_HTM[7662]="*“handa mayaṃ, bhante, buddhavacanaṃ chandaso āropemā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7663]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[7664]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after rebuking them …*";
P_HTM[7665]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[7666]="*“na, bhikkhave, buddhavacanaṃ chandaso āropetabbaṃ.**“You should not give metrical form to the word of the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7667]="*Yo āropeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7668]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, sakāya niruttiyā buddhavacanaṃ pariyāpuṇitun”ti.**You should learn the word of the Buddha using its own expressions.”*";
P_HTM[7669]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū lokāyataṃ pariyāpuṇanti.**At that time the monks from the group of six were learning cosmology.*";
P_HTM[7670]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7671]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[7672]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those lay people*";
P_HTM[7673]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**and they told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7674]="*“Api nu kho, bhikkhave, lokāyate sāradassāvī imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ viruḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjeyyā”ti?**“Is there any growth and fulfillment on this spiritual path, monks, for one who sees cosmology as the essence?”*";
P_HTM[7675]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“Certainly not.”*";
P_HTM[7676]="*“Imasmiṃ vā pana dhammavinaye sāradassāvī lokāyataṃ pariyāpuṇeyyā”ti?**“Would anyone who sees this spiritual path as the essence learn cosmology?”*";
P_HTM[7677]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“Certainly not.”*";
P_HTM[7678]="*“Na, bhikkhave, lokāyataṃ pariyāpuṇitabbaṃ.**“You should not learn cosmology.*";
P_HTM[7679]="*Yo pariyāpuṇeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7680]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū lokāyataṃ vācenti.**The monks from the group of six taught cosmology.*";
P_HTM[7681]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7682]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[7683]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7684]="*“Na, bhikkhave, lokāyataṃ vācetabbaṃ.**“You should not teach cosmology.*";
P_HTM[7685]="*Yo vāceyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7686]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū tiracchānavijjaṃ pariyāpuṇanti.**The monks from the group of six studied pointless knowledge.*";
P_HTM[7687]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7688]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[7689]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those lay people and they told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7690]="*“Na, bhikkhave, tiracchānavijjā pariyāpuṇitabbā.**“You should not study pointless knowledge.*";
P_HTM[7691]="*Yo pariyāpuṇeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7692]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū tiracchānavijjaṃ vācenti.**The monks from the group of six taught pointless knowledge.*";
P_HTM[7693]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7694]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[7695]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7696]="*“Na, bhikkhave, tiracchānavijjā vācetabbā.**“You should not teach pointless knowledge.*";
P_HTM[7697]="*Yo vāceyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7698]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā mahatiyā parisāya parivuto dhammaṃ desento khipi.**On one occasion the Buddha sneezed while teaching a large gathering.*";
P_HTM[7699]="*Bhikkhū—**The monks made an uproar, saying,*";
P_HTM[7700]="*“jīvatu, bhante, bhagavā;**“Long live the Buddha!”*";
P_HTM[7701]="*jīvatu sugato”ti—* **";
P_HTM[7702]="*uccāsaddaṃ mahāsaddaṃ akaṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[7703]="*Tena saddena dhammakathā antarā ahosi.**Because of the noise, the teaching was interrupted.*";
P_HTM[7704]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi—**The Buddha said to the monks:*";
P_HTM[7705]="*“api nu kho, bhikkhave, khipite ‘jīvā’ti vutto tappaccayā jīveyya vā mareyya vā”ti?**“If you say, ‘May you live long!’ to one who sneezes, will he live or die because of that?”*";
P_HTM[7706]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“Certainly not.”*";
P_HTM[7707]="*“Na, bhikkhave, khipite ‘jīvā’ti vattabbo.**“You should not say, ‘May you live long!’ to one who sneezes.*";
P_HTM[7708]="*Yo vadeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7709]="*Tena kho pana samayena manussā bhikkhūnaṃ khipite “jīvatha, bhante”ti vadanti.**At that time when monks sneezed, people said, “May you live long, Venerable!”*";
P_HTM[7710]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nālapanti.**Being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not respond.*";
P_HTM[7711]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7712]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā ‘jīvatha, bhante’ti vuccamānā nālapissantī”ti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics not respond when spoken to like this?”*";
P_HTM[7713]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7714]="*“Gihī, bhikkhave, maṅgalikā.**“Householders want blessings.*";
P_HTM[7715]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gihīnaṃ ‘jīvatha, bhante’ti vuccamānena ‘ciraṃ jīvā’ti vattun”ti.**When householders say, ‘May you live long!’ I allow you to respond with similar words.”*";
P_HTM[7716]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā mahatiyā parisāya parivuto dhammaṃ desento nisinno hoti.**On one occasion when the Buddha was seated teaching a large gathering,*";
P_HTM[7717]="*Aññatarena bhikkhunā lasuṇaṃ khāyitaṃ hoti.**there was a monk who had eaten garlic.*";
P_HTM[7718]="*So—* **";
P_HTM[7719]="*mā bhikkhū byābādhiṃsūti—**Not to annoy the other monks,*";
P_HTM[7720]="*ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**he had sat down at a distance.*";
P_HTM[7721]="*Addasā kho bhagavā taṃ bhikkhuṃ ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ.**The Buddha saw him*";
P_HTM[7722]="*Disvāna bhikkhū āmantesi—**and asked the monks why he was sitting there.*";
P_HTM[7723]="*“kiṃ nu kho so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ekamantaṃ nisinno”ti?**The monks told him and the Buddha said,*";
P_HTM[7724]="*“Etena, bhante, bhikkhunā lasuṇaṃ khāyitaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7725]="*So—* **";
P_HTM[7726]="*mā bhikkhū byābādhiṃsūti—* **";
P_HTM[7727]="*ekamantaṃ nisinno”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7728]="*“Api nu kho, bhikkhave, taṃ khāditabbaṃ, yaṃ khāditvā evarūpāya dhammakathāya paribāhiyo assā”ti?**“Monks, should one eat anything that would stop one from hearing a teaching such as this?”*";
P_HTM[7729]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“Certainly not.”*";
P_HTM[7730]="*“Na, bhikkhave, lasuṇaṃ khāditabbaṃ.**“You should not eat garlic.*";
P_HTM[7731]="*Yo khādeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7732]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato sāriputtassa udaravātābādho hoti.**On one occasion Venerable Sāriputta had a stomach ache.*";
P_HTM[7733]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca—**Venerable Mahāmoggallāna went to him and said,*";
P_HTM[7734]="*“pubbe te, āvuso sāriputta, udaravātābādho kena phāsu hotī”ti?**“When you had a stomach ache in the past, Sāriputta, what made you better?” —*";
P_HTM[7735]="*“Lasuṇena me, āvuso”ti.**“Garlic.”*";
P_HTM[7736]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7737]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ābādhappaccayā lasuṇaṃ khāditun”ti.**“I allow you to eat garlic if you are sick.”*";
P_HTM[7738]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū ārāme tahaṃ tahaṃ passāvaṃ karonti.**At that time the monks urinated here and there in the monastery.*";
P_HTM[7739]="*Ārāmo dussati.**The monastery became unclean.*";
P_HTM[7740]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7741]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ekamantaṃ passāvaṃ kātun”ti.**“You should urinate in one place.”*";
P_HTM[7742]="*Ārāmo duggandho hoti …pe…**The monastery became smelly.*";
P_HTM[7743]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, passāvakumbhin”ti.**“I allow a urine-collection pot.”*";
P_HTM[7744]="*Dukkhaṃ nisinnā passāvaṃ karonti …pe…**It was painful to sit there while urinating.*";
P_HTM[7745]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, passāvapādukan”ti.**“I allow foot-stands for urinating.”*";
P_HTM[7746]="*Passāvapādukā pākaṭā honti.**The foot-stands were unenclosed.*";
P_HTM[7747]="*Bhikkhū hiriyanti passāvaṃ kātuṃ …pe…**The monks were embarrassed to urinate there.*";
P_HTM[7748]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, parikkhipituṃ tayo pākāre—**“I allow three kinds of encircling walls:*";
P_HTM[7749]="*iṭṭhakāpākāraṃ, silāpākāraṃ, dārupākāran”ti.**a brick wall, a stone wall, and a wooden wall.”*";
P_HTM[7750]="*Passāvakumbhī apārutā duggandhā hoti …pe…**The urine-collection pot was not covered. It was smelly.*";
P_HTM[7751]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, apidhānan”ti.**“I allow a lid.”*";
P_HTM[7752]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū ārāme tahaṃ tahaṃ vaccaṃ karonti.**At that time the monks defecated here and there in the monastery.*";
P_HTM[7753]="*Ārāmo dussati.**The monastery became filthy.*";
P_HTM[7754]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7755]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ekamantaṃ vaccaṃ kātun”ti.**“You should defecate in one place.”*";
P_HTM[7756]="*Ārāmo duggandho hoti …pe…**The monastery became smelly.*";
P_HTM[7757]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, vaccakūpan”ti.**“I allow a cesspit.”*";
P_HTM[7758]="*Vaccakūpassa kūlaṃ lujjati …pe…**The edge of the cesspit collapsed.*";
P_HTM[7759]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cinituṃ tayo caye—**“I allow you to construct three kinds of foundations:*";
P_HTM[7760]="*iṭṭhakācayaṃ, silācayaṃ, dārucayan”ti.**a foundation of brick, a foundation of stone, and a foundation of wood.”*";
P_HTM[7761]="*Vaccakūpo nīcavatthuko hoti, udakena otthariyyati …pe…**The cesspit was situated on a low site. It was flooded.*";
P_HTM[7762]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, uccavatthukaṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to make a high base.”*";
P_HTM[7763]="*Cayo paripatati …pe…**The mound collapsed.*";
P_HTM[7764]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cinituṃ tayo caye—**“I allow you to construct three kinds of raised foundations:*";
P_HTM[7765]="*iṭṭhakācayaṃ, silācayaṃ, dārucayan”ti.**a raised foundation of brick, a raised foundation of stone, and a raised foundation of wood.”*";
P_HTM[7766]="*Ārohantā vihaññanti …pe…**It was difficult to get up to the cesspit.*";
P_HTM[7767]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tayo sopāne—**“I allow three kinds of stairs:*";
P_HTM[7768]="*iṭṭhakāsopānaṃ, silāsopānaṃ, dārusopānan”ti.**stairs of brick, stairs of stone, and stairs of wood.”*";
P_HTM[7769]="*Ārohantā paripatanti …pe…**People fell down while climbing the stairs.*";
P_HTM[7770]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ālambanabāhan”ti.**“I allow rails.”*";
P_HTM[7771]="*Ante nisinnā vaccaṃ karontā paripatanti …pe…**When seated on the edge to defecate, they fell down.*";
P_HTM[7772]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, santharitvā majjhe chiddaṃ katvā vaccaṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to lay a floor with a gap in the middle for defecating.”*";
P_HTM[7773]="*Dukkhaṃ nisinnā vaccaṃ karonti …pe…**It was painful to sit there while defecating.*";
P_HTM[7774]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, vaccapādukan”ti.**“I allow foot-stands for defecating.”*";
P_HTM[7775]="*Bahiddhā passāvaṃ karonti …pe…**They urinated outside the cesspit.*";
P_HTM[7776]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, passāvadoṇikan”ti.**“I allow a urinal.”*";
P_HTM[7777]="*Avalekhanakaṭṭhaṃ na hoti …pe…**There were no wiping sticks.*";
P_HTM[7778]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, avalekhanakaṭṭhan”ti.**“I allow wiping sticks.”*";
P_HTM[7779]="*Avalekhanapiṭharo na hoti …pe…**There was no container for the wiping sticks.*";
P_HTM[7780]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, avalekhanapiṭharan”ti.**“I allow a container for wiping sticks.”*";
P_HTM[7781]="*Vaccakūpo apāruto duggandho hoti …pe…**The cesspit was not covered and it was smelly.*";
P_HTM[7782]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, apidhānan”ti.**“I allow a lid.”*";
P_HTM[7783]="*Ajjhokāse vaccaṃ karontā sītenapi uṇhenapi kilamanti …pe…**Because they were defecating outside, the monks were afflicted by cold and heat.*";
P_HTM[7784]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, vaccakuṭin”ti.**“I allow a restroom.”*";
P_HTM[7785]="*Vaccakuṭiyā kavāṭaṃ na hoti …pe…**The restroom had no door.*";
P_HTM[7786]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kavāṭaṃ piṭṭhasaṅghāṭaṃ udukkhalikaṃ uttarapāsakaṃ aggaḷavaṭṭiṃ kapisīsakaṃ sūcikaṃ ghaṭikaṃ tāḷacchiddaṃ āviñchanacchiddaṃ āviñchanarajjun”ti.**“I allow a door, a door frame, a lower hinge, an upper hinge, a bolt-receiving post, a bolt socket, a bolt, an upper bolt, a keyhole, a door-pulling hole, and a door-pulling rope.”*";
P_HTM[7787]="*Vaccakuṭiyā tiṇacuṇṇaṃ paripatati …pe…**Grass and dust fell into the restroom.*";
P_HTM[7788]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ogumphetvā ullittāvalittaṃ kātuṃ—**“I allow you to firm up the structure and then to plaster it inside and outside, including:*";
P_HTM[7789]="*setavaṇṇaṃ kāḷavaṇṇaṃ gerukaparikammaṃ mālākammaṃ latākammaṃ makaradantakaṃ pañcapaṭikaṃ cīvaravaṃsaṃ cīvararajjun”ti.**treating with white color, black color, and red ocher; making a garland pattern, a creeper pattern, a shark-teeth pattern, and the fivefold pattern; putting up a bamboo robe rack and a clothesline.”*";
P_HTM[7790]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu jarādubbalo vaccaṃ katvā vuṭṭhahanto paripatati.**On one occasion a monk who was weak from old age fell over as he was getting up after defecating.*";
P_HTM[7791]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7792]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, olambakan”ti.**“I allow a suspended rope to hold onto.”*";
P_HTM[7793]="*Vaccakuṭi aparikkhittā hoti …pe…**The restroom was unenclosed.*";
P_HTM[7794]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, parikkhipituṃ tayo pākāre—**“I allow three kinds of encircling walls:*";
P_HTM[7795]="*iṭṭhakāpākāraṃ, silāpākāraṃ, dārupākāran”ti.**a brick wall, a stone wall, and a wooden wall.”*";
P_HTM[7796]="*Koṭṭhako na hoti …pe…**There was no gateway.*";
P_HTM[7797]="*“ anujānāmi, bhikkhave, koṭṭhakan”ti.**“I allow a gateway.”*";
P_HTM[7798]="*Koṭṭhakassa kavāṭaṃ na hoti …pe…**The gateway had no door.*";
P_HTM[7799]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kavāṭaṃ piṭṭhasaṅghāṭaṃ udukkhalikaṃ uttarapāsakaṃ aggaḷavaṭṭiṃ kapisīsakaṃ sūcikaṃ ghaṭikaṃ tāḷacchiddaṃ āviñchanacchiddaṃ āviñchanarajjun”ti.**“I allow a door, a door frame, a lower hinge, an upper hinge, a bolt-receiving post, a bolt socket, a bolt, an upper bolt, a keyhole, a door-pulling hole, and a door-pulling rope.”*";
P_HTM[7800]="*Koṭṭhake tiṇacuṇṇaṃ paripatati …pe…**Grass and dust fell into the gateway.*";
P_HTM[7801]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ogumphetvā ullittāvalittaṃ kātuṃ—**“I allow you to firm up the structure and then plaster it inside and outside, including:*";
P_HTM[7802]="*setavaṇṇaṃ kāḷavaṇṇaṃ gerukaparikammaṃ mālākammaṃ latākammaṃ makaradantakaṃ pañcapaṭikan”ti.**treating with white color, black color, and red ocher; making a garland pattern, a creeper pattern, a shark-teeth pattern, and the fivefold pattern.”*";
P_HTM[7803]="*Pariveṇaṃ cikkhallaṃ hoti …pe…**The precincts were muddy.*";
P_HTM[7804]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, marumbaṃ pakiritun”ti.**“I allow you to cover it with gravel.”*";
P_HTM[7805]="*Na pariyāpuṇanti …pe…**They were unable to do it.*";
P_HTM[7806]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, padarasilaṃ nikkhipitun”ti.**“I allow you to lay down paving stones.”*";
P_HTM[7807]="*Udakaṃ santiṭṭhati …pe…**The water remained.*";
P_HTM[7808]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, udakaniddhamanan”ti.**“I allow a water drain.”*";
P_HTM[7809]="*Ācamanakumbhī na hoti …pe…**There was no pot for rinsing water.*";
P_HTM[7810]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ācamanakumbhin”ti.**“I allow a pot for rinsing water.”*";
P_HTM[7811]="*Ācamanasarāvako na hoti …pe…**There was no scoop for the rinsing water.*";
P_HTM[7812]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ācamanasarāvakan”ti.**“I allow a scoop for the rinsing water.”*";
P_HTM[7813]="*Dukkhaṃ nisinnā ācamenti …pe…**It was painful to sit there while rinsing.*";
P_HTM[7814]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ācamanapādukan”ti.**“I allow foot-stands for rinsing.”*";
P_HTM[7815]="*Ācamanapādukā pākaṭā honti, bhikkhū hiriyanti ācametuṃ …pe…**The foot-stands were unenclosed. The monks were embarrassed to rinse there.*";
P_HTM[7816]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, parikkhipituṃ tayo pākāre—**“I allow three kinds of encircling wall:*";
P_HTM[7817]="*iṭṭhakāpākāraṃ, silāpākāraṃ, dārupākāran”ti.**a brick wall, a stone wall, or a wooden wall.”*";
P_HTM[7818]="*Ācamanakumbhī apārutā hoti, tiṇacuṇṇehipi paṃsukehipi okiriyyati …pe…**The rinsing-water pot was not covered. Grass, dust, and dirt fell into it.*";
P_HTM[7819]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, apidhānan”ti.**“I allow a lid.”*";
P_HTM[7820]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū evarūpaṃ anācāraṃ ācaranti—**At one time the monks from the group of six were misbehaving in many ways.*";
P_HTM[7821]="*mālāvacchaṃ ropentipi ropāpentipi, siñcantipi siñcāpentipi, ocinantipi ocināpentipi, ganthentipi ganthāpentipi, ekatovaṇṭikamālaṃ karontipi kārāpentipi, ubhatovaṇṭikamālaṃ karontipi kārāpentipi, mañjarikaṃ karontipi kārāpentipi, vidhūtikaṃ karontipi kārāpentipi, vaṭaṃsakaṃ karontipi kārāpentipi, āveḷaṃ karontipi kārāpentipi, uracchadaṃ karontipi kārāpentipi.**They planted flowering trees, watered and plucked them, and then tied the flowers together. They made the flowers into garlands, garlands with stalks on one side and garlands with stalks on both sides. They made flower arrangements, wreaths, ornaments for the head, ornaments for the ears, and ornaments for the chest. And they had others do the same.*";
P_HTM[7822]="*Te kulitthīnaṃ kuladhītānaṃ kulakumārīnaṃ kulasuṇhānaṃ kuladāsīnaṃ ekatovaṇṭikamālaṃ harantipi harāpentipi, ubhatovaṇṭikamālaṃ harantipi harāpentipi, mañjarikaṃ harantipi harāpentipi, vidhūtikaṃ harantipi harāpentipi, vaṭaṃsakaṃ harantipi harāpentipi, āveḷaṃ harantipi harāpentipi, uracchadaṃ harantipi harāpentipi.**They then took these things, or sent them, to the women, the daughters, the girls, the daughters-in-law, and the female slaves of good families.*";
P_HTM[7823]="*Te kulitthīhi kuladhītāhi kulakumārīhi kulasuṇhāhi kuladāsīhi saddhiṃ ekabhājanepi bhuñjanti, ekathālakepi pivanti, ekāsanepi nisīdanti, ekamañcepi tuvaṭṭenti, ekattharaṇāpi tuvaṭṭenti, ekapāvuraṇāpi tuvaṭṭenti, ekattharaṇapāvuraṇāpi tuvaṭṭenti, vikālepi bhuñjanti, majjampi pivanti, mālāgandhavilepanampi dhārenti, naccantipi, gāyantipi, vādentipi, lāsentipi;**They ate from the same plates as these women and drank from the same vessels. They sat on the same seats as them, and they lay down on the same beds, on the same sheets, under the same covers, and both on the same sheets and under the same covers. They ate at the wrong time, drank alcohol, and wore garlands, perfumes, and cosmetics. They danced, sang, played instruments, and performed.*";
P_HTM[7824]="*naccantiyāpi naccanti, naccantiyāpi gāyanti, naccantiyāpi vādenti, naccantiyāpi lāsenti …pe…**While the women were dancing, singing, playing instruments, and performing,*";
P_HTM[7825]="*lāsentiyāpi naccanti, lāsentiyāpi gāyanti, lāsentiyāpi vādenti, lāsentiyāpi lāsenti;**so would they.*";
P_HTM[7826]="*aṭṭhapadepi kīḷanti, dasapadepi kīḷanti, ākāsepi kīḷanti, parihārapathepi kīḷanti, santikāyapi kīḷanti, khalikāyapi kīḷanti, ghaṭikāyapi kīḷanti, salākahatthenapi kīḷanti, akkhenapi kīḷanti, paṅgacīrenapi kīḷanti, vaṅkakenapi kīḷanti, mokkhacikāyapi kīḷanti, ciṅgulakenapi kīḷanti, pattāḷhakenapi kīḷanti, rathakenapi kīḷanti, dhanukenapi kīḷanti, akkharikāyapi kīḷanti, manesikāyapi kīḷanti, yathāvajjenapi kīḷanti;**They played various games: eight-row checkers, ten-row checkers, imaginary checkers, hopscotch, spillikins, dice, tip-cat, painting with the hand, ball games, leaf flutes, toy plows, somersaults, toy windmills, toy measures, toy carriages, toy bows, letter guessing, thought guessing, mimicking deformities.*";
P_HTM[7827]="*hatthismimpi sikkhanti, assasmimpi sikkhanti, rathasmimpi sikkhanti, dhanusmimpi sikkhanti;**They trained in elephant riding, in horsemanship, in carriage riding, in archery,*";
P_HTM[7828]="*tharusmimpi sikkhanti;**in swordsmanship.*";
P_HTM[7829]="*hatthissapi purato dhāvanti, assassapi purato dhāvanti, rathassapi purato dhāvantipi ādhāvantipi;**And they ran in front of elephants, horses, and carriages, and they ran backward and forward.*";
P_HTM[7830]="*usseḷentipi, apphoṭentipi, nibbujjhantipi, muṭṭhīhipi yujjhanti;**They whistled, clapped their hands, wrestled, and boxed.*";
P_HTM[7831]="*raṅgamajjhepi saṅghāṭiṃ pattharitvā naccakiṃ evaṃ vadanti—**They spread their outer robes on a stage and said to the dancing girls,*";
P_HTM[7832]="*“idha, bhagini, naccassū”ti;**“Dance here, Sister,”*";
P_HTM[7833]="*nalāṭikampi denti;**and they made gestures of approval.*";
P_HTM[7834]="*vividhampi anācāraṃ ācaranti.**And they engaged in many kinds of misbehavior.*";
P_HTM[7835]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[7836]="*“na, bhikkhave, vividhaṃ anācāraṃ ācaritabbaṃ.**“You should not engage in various kinds of misbehavior*";
P_HTM[7837]="*Yo ācareyya, yathādhammo kāretabbo”ti.**If you do, you should be dealt with according to the rule.”*";
P_HTM[7838]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmante uruvelakassape pabbajite saṅghassa bahuṃ lohabhaṇḍaṃ dārubhaṇḍaṃ mattikābhaṇḍaṃ uppannaṃ hoti.**At the time of Venerable Uruvelakassapa’s going forth, the Sangha was given a large number of iron goods, wooden goods, and ceramic goods.*";
P_HTM[7839]="*Atha kho bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The monks thought,*";
P_HTM[7840]="*“kiṃ nu kho bhagavatā lohabhaṇḍaṃ anuññātaṃ, kiṃ ananuññātaṃ;**“Which iron,*";
P_HTM[7841]="*kiṃ dārubhaṇḍaṃ anuññātaṃ, kiṃ ananuññātaṃ;**wooden,*";
P_HTM[7842]="*kiṃ mattikābhaṇḍaṃ anuññātaṃ, kiṃ ananuññātan”ti?**and ceramic goods have been allowed by the Buddha, and which not?”*";
P_HTM[7843]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7844]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**The Buddha then gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[7845]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ṭhapetvā paharaṇiṃ sabbaṃ lohabhaṇḍaṃ, ṭhapetvā āsandiṃ pallaṅkaṃ dārupattaṃ dārupādukaṃ sabbaṃ dārubhaṇḍaṃ, ṭhapetvā katakañca kumbhakārikañca sabbaṃ mattikābhaṇḍan”ti.**“I allow all iron goods except weapons; all wooden goods except high couches, luxurious couches, wooden almsbowls, and wooden shoes; and all ceramic goods except ceramic foot scrubbers and clay huts.”*";
P_HTM[7846]="*Khuddakavatthukkhandhako pañcamo.**The fifth chapter with short topics is finished.*";
P_HTM[7847]="*Tassuddānaṃ* **";
P_HTM[7848]="*Rukkhe thambhe ca kuṭṭe ca,* **";
P_HTM[7849]="*aṭṭāne gandhasuttiyā;* **";
P_HTM[7850]="*Vigayha mallako kacchu,* **";
P_HTM[7851]="*jarā ca puthupāṇikā.* **";
P_HTM[7852]="*Vallikāpi ca pāmaṅgo,* **";
P_HTM[7853]="*kaṇṭhasuttaṃ na dhāraye;* **";
P_HTM[7854]="*Kaṭi ovaṭṭi kāyuraṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7855]="*hatthābharaṇamuddikā.* **";
P_HTM[7856]="*Dīghe kocche phaṇe hatthe,* **";
P_HTM[7857]="*sitthā udakatelake;* **";
P_HTM[7858]="*Ādāsudapattavaṇā,* **";
P_HTM[7859]="*ālepommaddacuṇṇanā.* **";
P_HTM[7860]="*Lañchenti aṅgarāgañca,* **";
P_HTM[7861]="*mukharāgaṃ tadūbhayaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[7862]="*Cakkhurogaṃ giraggañca,* **";
P_HTM[7863]="*āyataṃ sarabāhiraṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7864]="*Ambapesisakalehi,* **";
P_HTM[7865]="*ahicchindi ca candanaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[7866]="*Uccāvacā pattamūlā,* **";
P_HTM[7867]="*suvaṇṇo bahalā valī.* **";
P_HTM[7868]="*Citrā dussati duggandho,* **";
P_HTM[7869]="*uṇhe bhijjiṃsu miḍḍhiyā;* **";
P_HTM[7870]="*Paribhaṇḍaṃ tiṇaṃ coḷaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7871]="*mālaṃ kuṇḍolikāya ca.* **";
P_HTM[7872]="*Thavikā aṃsabaddhañca,* **";
P_HTM[7873]="*tathā bandhanasuttakā;* **";
P_HTM[7874]="*Khile mañce ca pīṭhe ca,* **";
P_HTM[7875]="*aṅke chatte paṇāmanā.* **";
P_HTM[7876]="*Tumbaghaṭichavasīsaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7877]="*calakāni paṭiggaho;* **";
P_HTM[7878]="*Vipphālidaṇḍasovaṇṇaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7879]="*patte pesi ca nāḷikā.* **";
P_HTM[7880]="*Kiṇṇasattu saritañca,* **";
P_HTM[7881]="*madhusitthaṃ sipāṭikaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[7882]="*Vikaṇṇaṃ bandhivisamaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7883]="*chamājirapahoti ca.* **";
P_HTM[7884]="*Kaḷimbhaṃ moghasuttañca,* **";
P_HTM[7885]="*adhotallaṃ upāhanā;* **";
P_HTM[7886]="*Aṅgule paṭiggahañca,* **";
P_HTM[7887]="*vitthakaṃ thavikabaddhakā.* **";
P_HTM[7888]="*Ajjhokāse nīcavatthu,* **";
P_HTM[7889]="*cayo cāpi vihaññare;* **";
P_HTM[7890]="*Paripati tiṇacuṇṇaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7891]="*ullittaavalittakaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7892]="*Setaṃ kāḷakavaṇṇañca,* **";
P_HTM[7893]="*parikammañca gerukaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[7894]="*Mālākammaṃ latākammaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7895]="*makaradantakapāṭikaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7896]="*Cīvaravaṃsaṃ rajjuñca,* **";
P_HTM[7897]="*anuññāsi vināyako;* **";
P_HTM[7898]="*Ujjhitvā pakkamanti ca,* **";
P_HTM[7899]="*kathinaṃ paribhijjati.* **";
P_HTM[7900]="*Viniveṭhiyati kuṭṭepi,* **";
P_HTM[7901]="*pattenādāya gacchare;* **";
P_HTM[7902]="*Thavikā bandhasuttañca,* **";
P_HTM[7903]="*bandhitvā ca upāhanā.* **";
P_HTM[7904]="*Upāhanatthavikañca,* **";
P_HTM[7905]="*aṃsabaddhañca suttakaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[7906]="*Udakākappiyaṃ magge,* **";
P_HTM[7907]="*parissāvanacoḷakaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7908]="*Dhammakaraṇaṃ dve bhikkhū,* **";
P_HTM[7909]="*vesāliṃ agamā muni;* **";
P_HTM[7910]="*Daṇḍaṃ ottharakaṃ tattha,* **";
P_HTM[7911]="*anuññāsi parissāvanaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7912]="*Makasehi paṇītena,* **";
P_HTM[7913]="*bahvābādhā ca jīvako;* **";
P_HTM[7914]="*Caṅkamanajantāgharaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7915]="*visame nīcavatthuko.* **";
P_HTM[7916]="*Tayo caye vihaññanti,* **";
P_HTM[7917]="*sopānālambavedikaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[7918]="*Ajjhokāse tiṇacuṇṇaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7919]="*ullittaavalittakaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7920]="*Setakaṃ kāḷavaṇṇañca,* **";
P_HTM[7921]="*parikammañca gerukaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[7922]="*Mālākammaṃ latākammaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7923]="*makaradantakapāṭikaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7924]="*Vaṃsaṃ cīvararajjuñca,* **";
P_HTM[7925]="*uccañca vatthukaṃ kare;* **";
P_HTM[7926]="*Cayo sopānabāhañca,* **";
P_HTM[7927]="*kavāṭaṃ piṭṭhasaṅghāṭaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7928]="*Udukkhaluttarapāsakaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7929]="*vaṭṭiñca kapisīsakaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[7930]="*Sūcighaṭitāḷacchiddaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7931]="*āviñchanañca rajjukaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7932]="*Maṇḍalaṃ dhūmanettañca,* **";
P_HTM[7933]="*majjhe ca mukhamattikā;* **";
P_HTM[7934]="*Doṇi duggandhā dahati,* **";
P_HTM[7935]="*udakaṭṭhānaṃ sarāvakaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7936]="*Na sedeti ca cikkhallaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7937]="*dhovi niddhamanaṃ kare;* **";
P_HTM[7938]="*Pīṭhañca koṭṭhake kammaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7939]="*marumbā silā niddhamanaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7940]="*Naggā chamāya vassante,* **";
P_HTM[7941]="*paṭicchādī tayo tahiṃ;* **";
P_HTM[7942]="*Udapānaṃ lujjati nīcaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7943]="*valliyā kāyabandhane.* **";
P_HTM[7944]="*Tulaṃ kaṭakaṭaṃ cakkaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7945]="*bahū bhijjanti bhājanā;* **";
P_HTM[7946]="*Lohadārucammakhaṇḍaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7947]="*sālātiṇāpidhāni ca.* **";
P_HTM[7948]="*Doṇicandani pākāraṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7949]="*cikkhallaṃ niddhamanena ca;* **";
P_HTM[7950]="*Sītigataṃ pokkharaṇiṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7951]="*purāṇañca nillekhaṇaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7952]="*Cātumāsaṃ sayanti ca,* **";
P_HTM[7953]="*namatakañca nadhiṭṭhahe;* **";
P_HTM[7954]="*Āsittakaṃ maḷorikaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7955]="*bhuñjantekaṃ tuvaṭṭeyyuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7956]="*Vaḍḍho bodhi na akkami,* **";
P_HTM[7957]="*ghaṭaṃ katakasammajjani;* **";
P_HTM[7958]="*Sakkharaṃ kathalañceva,* **";
P_HTM[7959]="*pheṇakaṃ pādaghaṃsanī.* **";
P_HTM[7960]="*Vidhūpanaṃ tālavaṇṭaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7961]="*makasañcāpi cāmarī;* **";
P_HTM[7962]="*Chattaṃ vinā ca ārāme,* **";
P_HTM[7963]="*tayo sikkāya sammuti.* **";
P_HTM[7964]="*Romasitthā nakhā dīghā,* **";
P_HTM[7965]="*chindantaṅgulikā dukkhā;* **";
P_HTM[7966]="*Salohitaṃ pamāṇañca,* **";
P_HTM[7967]="*vīsati dīghakesatā.* **";
P_HTM[7968]="*Khuraṃ silaṃ sipāṭikaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7969]="*namatakaṃ khurabhaṇḍakaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[7970]="*Massuṃ kappenti vaḍḍhenti,* **";
P_HTM[7971]="*golomicaturassakaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7972]="*Parimukhaṃ aḍḍhadukañca,* **";
P_HTM[7973]="*dāṭhisambādhasaṃhare;* **";
P_HTM[7974]="*Ābādhā kattarivaṇo,* **";
P_HTM[7975]="*dīghaṃ sakkharikāya ca.* **";
P_HTM[7976]="*Palitaṃ thakitaṃ uccā,* **";
P_HTM[7977]="*lohabhaṇḍañjanī saha;* **";
P_HTM[7978]="*Pallatthikañca āyogo,* **";
P_HTM[7979]="*vaṭaṃ salākabandhanaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7980]="*Kalābukaṃ deḍḍubhakaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7981]="*murajaṃ maddavīṇakaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[7982]="*Paṭṭikā sūkarantañca,* **";
P_HTM[7983]="*dasā murajaveṇikā;* **";
P_HTM[7984]="*Anto sobhaṃ guṇakañca,* **";
P_HTM[7985]="*pavanantopi jīrati.* **";
P_HTM[7986]="*Gaṇṭhikā uccāvacañca,* **";
P_HTM[7987]="*phalakantepi ogāhe;* **";
P_HTM[7988]="*Gihivatthaṃ hatthisoṇḍaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7989]="*macchakaṃ catukaṇṇakaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7990]="*Tālavaṇṭaṃ satavali,* **";
P_HTM[7991]="*gihipārutapārupaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[7992]="*Saṃvelli ubhatokājaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7993]="*dantakaṭṭhaṃ ākoṭane.* **";
P_HTM[7994]="*Kaṇṭhe vilaggaṃ dāyañca,* **";
P_HTM[7995]="*paṭaggi rukkhahatthinā;* **";
P_HTM[7996]="*Yameḷe lokāyatakaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[7997]="*pariyāpuṇiṃsu vācayuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7998]="*Tiracchānakathā vijjā,* **";
P_HTM[7999]="*khipi maṅgalaṃ khādi ca;* **";
P_HTM[8000]="*Vātābādho dussati ca,* **";
P_HTM[8001]="*duggandho dukkhapādukā.* **";
P_HTM[8002]="*Hiriyanti pāruduggandho,* **";
P_HTM[8003]="*tahaṃ tahaṃ karonti ca;* **";
P_HTM[8004]="*Duggandho kūpaṃ lujjanti,* **";
P_HTM[8005]="*uccavatthu cayena ca.* **";
P_HTM[8006]="*Sopānālambanabāhā,* **";
P_HTM[8007]="*ante dukkhañca pādukā;* **";
P_HTM[8008]="*Bahiddhā doṇi kaṭṭhañca,* **";
P_HTM[8009]="*piṭharo ca apāruto.* **";
P_HTM[8010]="*Vaccakuṭiṃ kavāṭañca,* **";
P_HTM[8011]="*piṭṭhasaṅghāṭameva ca;* **";
P_HTM[8012]="*Udukkhaluttarapāso,* **";
P_HTM[8013]="*vaṭṭiñca kapisīsakaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8014]="*Sūcighaṭitāḷacchiddaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[8015]="*āviñchanacchiddameva ca;* **";
P_HTM[8016]="*Rajju ullittāvalittaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[8017]="*setavaṇṇañca kāḷakaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8018]="*Mālākammaṃ latākammaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[8019]="*makaraṃ pañcapaṭikaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[8020]="*Cīvaravaṃsaṃ rajjuñca,* **";
P_HTM[8021]="*jarādubbalapākāraṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8022]="*Koṭṭhake cāpi tatheva,* **";
P_HTM[8023]="*marumbaṃ padarasilā;* **";
P_HTM[8024]="*Santiṭṭhati niddhamanaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[8025]="*kumbhiñcāpi sarāvakaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8026]="*Dukkhaṃ hiri apidhānaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[8027]="*anācārañca ācaruṃ;* **";
P_HTM[8028]="*Lohabhaṇḍaṃ anuññāsi,* **";
P_HTM[8029]="*ṭhapayitvā paharaṇiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8030]="*Ṭhapayitvāsandipallaṅkaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[8031]="*dārupattañca pādukaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[8032]="*Sabbaṃ dārumayaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[8033]="*anuññāsi mahāmuni.* **";
P_HTM[8034]="*Katakaṃ kumbhakārañca,* **";
P_HTM[8035]="*ṭhapayitvā tathāgato;* **";
P_HTM[8036]="*Sabbampi mattikābhaṇḍaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[8037]="*anuññāsi anukampako.* **";
P_HTM[8038]="*Yassa vatthussa niddeso,**The details of the topics,*";
P_HTM[8039]="*purimena yadi samaṃ;**If taken altogether with the previous,*";
P_HTM[8040]="*Tampi saṅkhittaṃ uddāne,**Is also found in brief in the summary verses,*";
P_HTM[8041]="*nayato taṃ vijāniyā.**For the purpose of guiding those who have understood it.*";
P_HTM[8042]="*Evaṃ dasasatā vatthū,**Thus there are one hundred and ten topics*";
P_HTM[8043]="*vinaye khuddakavatthuke;**In the Chapter on short topics in the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[8044]="*Saddhammaṭṭhitiko ceva,**Indeed, the true Teaching will be long lived,*";
P_HTM[8045]="*pesalānañcanuggaho.**And good people will be supported.*";
P_HTM[8046]="*Susikkhito vinayadharo,**A well-trained expert in the Monastic Law,*";
P_HTM[8047]="*hitacitto supesalo;**A good person intent on what’s beneficial,*";
P_HTM[8048]="*Padīpakaraṇo dhīro,**A wise one, lighting a lamp—*";
P_HTM[8049]="*pūjāraho bahussutoti.**This is a learned one worthy of homage.*";
P_HTM[8050]="*Khuddakavatthukkhandhako niṭṭhito.**The chapter with short topics is finished.*";
P_HTM[8051]="*6. Senāsanakkhandhaka **6.  The chapter on dwellings *";
P_HTM[8052]="*1. Vihārānujānana**1.1 The allowance for dwellings*";
P_HTM[8053]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[8054]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ senāsanaṃ apaññattaṃ hoti.**At this time the Buddha had not yet allowed dwellings.*";
P_HTM[8055]="*Te ca bhikkhū tahaṃ tahaṃ viharanti—**And the monks stayed here and there:*";
P_HTM[8056]="*araññe, rukkhamūle, pabbate, kandarāyaṃ, giriguhāyaṃ, susāne, vanapatthe, ajjhokāse, palālapuñje.**in the wilderness, at the foot of a tree, on a hill, in a gorge, in a hillside cave, in a charnel ground, in the forest, in the open, on a heap of straw.*";
P_HTM[8057]="*Te kālasseva tato tato upanikkhamanti—**Early in the morning, they would emerge from those places.*";
P_HTM[8058]="*araññā rukkhamūlā pabbatā kandarā giriguhā susānā vanapatthā ajjhokāsā palālapuñjā, pāsādikena abhikkantena paṭikkantena, ālokitena vilokitena, samiñjitena pasāritena, okkhittacakkhū, iriyāpathasampannā.**And they were pleasing in their conduct: in going out and coming back, in looking ahead and looking aside, in bending and stretching their arms. Their eyes were lowered, and they were perfect in deportment.*";
P_HTM[8059]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājagahako seṭṭhī kālasseva uyyānaṃ agamāsi.**One morning a wealthy merchant of Rājagaha was going to a park*";
P_HTM[8060]="*Addasā kho rājagahako seṭṭhī te bhikkhū kālasseva tato tato upanikkhamante—**when he saw those monks.*";
P_HTM[8061]="*araññā rukkhamūlā pabbatā kandarā giriguhā susānā vanapatthā ajjhokāsā palālapuñjā, pāsādikena abhikkantena paṭikkantena, ālokitena vilokitena, samiñjitena pasāritena, okkhittacakkhū, iriyāpathasampanne.* **";
P_HTM[8062]="*Disvānassa cittaṃ pasīdi.**Being inspired,*";
P_HTM[8063]="*Atha kho rājagahako seṭṭhī yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū etadavoca—**he approached them and said,*";
P_HTM[8064]="*“sacāhaṃ, bhante, vihāre kārāpeyyaṃ, vaseyyātha me vihāresū”ti?**“Venerables, if I build dwellings, would you stay there?”*";
P_HTM[8065]="*“Na kho, gahapati, bhagavatā vihārā anuññātā”ti.**“The Buddha hasn’t allowed dwellings.”*";
P_HTM[8066]="*“Tena hi, bhante, bhagavantaṃ paṭipucchitvā mama āroceyyāthā”ti.**“Well then, please ask the Buddha and let me know his response.”*";
P_HTM[8067]="*“Evaṃ, gahapatī”ti**“Yes.”*";
P_HTM[8068]="*kho te bhikkhū rājagahakassa seṭṭhissa paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu.**Those monks then went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[8069]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ—**and said,*";
P_HTM[8070]="*“rājagahako, bhante, seṭṭhī vihāre kārāpetukāmo.**“Venerable Sir, a wealthy merchant of Rājagaha wants to build dwellings.*";
P_HTM[8071]="*Kathaṃ nu kho, bhante, amhehi paṭipajjitabban”ti?**What should we do?”*";
P_HTM[8072]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[8073]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pañca leṇāni—**“I allow five kinds of shelters:*";
P_HTM[8074]="*vihāraṃ, aḍḍhayogaṃ, pāsādaṃ, hammiyaṃ, guhan”ti.**dwellings, three kinds of stilt houses, and caves.”*";
P_HTM[8075]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū yena rājagahako seṭṭhī tenupasaṅkamiṃsu, upasaṅkamitvā rājagahakaṃ seṭṭhiṃ etadavocuṃ—**The monks went to that merchant and said,*";
P_HTM[8076]="*“anuññātā kho, gahapati, bhagavatā vihārā;**“The Buddha has allowed dwellings.*";
P_HTM[8077]="*yassadāni kālaṃ maññasī”ti.**Please do whatever you think is appropriate.”*";
P_HTM[8078]="*Atha kho rājagahako seṭṭhī ekāheneva saṭṭhivihāre patiṭṭhāpesi.**Then, on a single day, that merchant built sixty dwellings.*";
P_HTM[8079]="*Atha kho rājagahako seṭṭhī te saṭṭhivihāre pariyosāpetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**When the dwellings were finished, he went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[8080]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho rājagahako seṭṭhī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[8081]="*“adhivāsetu me, bhante, bhagavā svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghenā”ti.**“Venerable Sir, please accept tomorrow’s meal from me, together with the Sangha of monks.”*";
P_HTM[8082]="*Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena.**The Buddha consented by remaining silent.*";
P_HTM[8083]="*Atha kho rājagahako seṭṭhī bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**Knowing that the Buddha had consented, he got up from his seat, bowed down, circumambulated the Buddha with his right side toward him, and left.*";
P_HTM[8084]="*Atha kho rājagahako seṭṭhī tassā rattiyā accayena paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā bhagavato kālaṃ ārocāpesi—**The next morning he had various kinds of fine food prepared and then had the Buddha informed*";
P_HTM[8085]="*“kālo, bhante, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan”ti.**that the meal was ready.*";
P_HTM[8086]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena rājagahakassa seṭṭhissa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghena.**After robing up, the Buddha took his bowl and robe and went to the house of that merchant, where he sat down on the prepared seat together with the Sangha of monks.*";
P_HTM[8087]="*Atha kho rājagahako seṭṭhī buddhappamukhaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappetvā sampavāretvā, bhagavantaṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ, ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**That merchant personally served various kinds of fine food to the Sangha of monks headed by the Buddha. When the Buddha had finished his meal and had washed his hands and bowl, the merchant sat down to one side*";
P_HTM[8088]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho rājagahako seṭṭhī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[8089]="*“ete me, bhante, saṭṭhivihārā puññatthikena saggatthikena kārāpitā.**“Sir, I’ve had these sixty dwellings built to make merit and for the purpose of going to heaven.*";
P_HTM[8090]="*Kathāhaṃ, bhante, tesu vihāresu paṭipajjāmī”ti?**What should I do now?”*";
P_HTM[8091]="*“Tena hi tvaṃ, gahapati, te saṭṭhivihāre āgatānāgatassa cātuddisassa saṅghassa patiṭṭhāpehī”ti.**“Well then, give those sixty dwellings to the Sangha everywhere, both present and future.”*";
P_HTM[8092]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho rājagahako seṭṭhī bhagavato paṭissutvā te saṭṭhivihāre āgatānāgatassa cātuddisassa saṅghassa patiṭṭhāpesi.**Saying, “Yes,” he did just that.*";
P_HTM[8093]="*Atha kho bhagavā rājagahakaṃ seṭṭhiṃ imāhi gāthāhi anumodi—**The Buddha then expressed his appreciation to the merchant with these verses:*";
P_HTM[8094]="*“Sītaṃ uṇhaṃ paṭihanti,**“Cold and heat are kept away,*";
P_HTM[8095]="*tato vāḷamigāni ca;**And predatory animals too,*";
P_HTM[8096]="*Sarīsape ca makase,**And creeping animals and mosquitoes,*";
P_HTM[8097]="*sisire cāpi vuṭṭhiyo.**And also chill and rain.*";
P_HTM[8098]="*Tato vātātapo ghoro,**It keeps away the wind and burning sun,*";
P_HTM[8099]="*sañjāto paṭihaññati;**When those awful things arise.*";
P_HTM[8100]="*Leṇatthañca sukhatthañca,**It’s for the sake of shelter and happiness,*";
P_HTM[8101]="*jhāyituñca vipassituṃ.**To attain absorption and to see clearly.*";
P_HTM[8102]="*Vihāradānaṃ saṅghassa,**Giving dwellings to the Sangha*";
P_HTM[8103]="*Aggaṃ buddhena vaṇṇitaṃ;**Is praised as the best by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[8104]="*Tasmā hi paṇḍito poso,**Therefore the wise man,*";
P_HTM[8105]="*Sampassaṃ atthamattano.**Seeing what is beneficial for himself,*";
P_HTM[8106]="*Vihāre kāraye ramme,**Should build delightful dwellings*";
P_HTM[8107]="*vāsayettha bahussute;**And have the learned stay there.*";
P_HTM[8108]="*Tesaṃ annañca pānañca,**Food, drink, robes, and dwellings—*";
P_HTM[8109]="*vatthasenāsanāni ca.**With an inspired mind,*";
P_HTM[8110]="*Dadeyya ujubhūtesu,**He should give to them,*";
P_HTM[8111]="*Vippasannena cetasā;**The upright ones.*";
P_HTM[8112]="*Te tassa dhammaṃ desenti,**They will give him the Teaching*";
P_HTM[8113]="*Sabbadukkhāpanūdanaṃ;**For removing all suffering;*";
P_HTM[8114]="*Yaṃ so dhammaṃ idhaññāya,**And understanding this Teaching in this life,*";
P_HTM[8115]="*Parinibbāti anāsavo”ti.**He attains extinguishment, free of corruptions.”*";
P_HTM[8116]="*Atha kho bhagavā rājagahakaṃ seṭṭhiṃ imāhi gāthāhi anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi.**The Buddha then got up from his seat and left.*";
P_HTM[8117]="*Assosuṃ kho manussā—**Hearing that the Buddha had allowed dwellings,*";
P_HTM[8118]="*“bhagavatā kira vihārā anuññātā”ti sakkaccaṃ vihāre kārāpenti.**people had dwellings built with care.*";
P_HTM[8119]="*Te vihārā akavāṭakā honti;**But because the dwellings did not have doors,*";
P_HTM[8120]="*ahīpi vicchikāpi satapadiyopi pavisanti.**snakes, scorpions, and centipedes came inside.*";
P_HTM[8121]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[8122]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kavāṭan”ti.**“I allow doors.”*";
P_HTM[8123]="*Bhittichiddaṃ karitvā valliyāpi rajjuyāpi kavāṭaṃ bandhanti.**They made a hole in the wall and bound the doors with creepers and ropes.*";
P_HTM[8124]="*Undūrehipi upacikāhipi khajjanti.**Rats and termites ate the creepers and ropes,*";
P_HTM[8125]="*Khayitabandhanāni kavāṭāni patanti.**and the doors fell off.*";
P_HTM[8126]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8127]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, piṭṭhasaṅghāṭaṃ udukkhalikaṃ uttarapāsakan”ti.**“I allow door frames, and lower and upper hinges.”*";
P_HTM[8128]="*Kavāṭā na phusīyanti.**The doors did not touch the door frames.*";
P_HTM[8129]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8130]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, āviñchanacchiddaṃ āviñchanarajjun”ti.**“I allow a hole in the door for pulling it and a rope for pulling it.”*";
P_HTM[8131]="*Kavāṭā na thakiyanti.**The doors did not stay closed.*";
P_HTM[8132]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8133]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, aggaḷavaṭṭiṃ kapisīsakaṃ sūcikaṃ ghaṭikan”ti.**“I allow bolt-receiving posts, bolt sockets, bolts, and upper bolts.”*";
P_HTM[8134]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū na sakkonti kavāṭaṃ apāpurituṃ.**The monks were not able to open the doors.*";
P_HTM[8135]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8136]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tāḷacchiddaṃ.**“I allow a keyhole*";
P_HTM[8137]="*Tīṇi tāḷāni—**and three kinds of keys:*";
P_HTM[8138]="*lohatāḷaṃ, kaṭṭhatāḷaṃ, visāṇatāḷan”ti.**metal keys, wooden keys, and keys made of horn.”*";
P_HTM[8139]="*Yehi te ugghāṭetvā pavisanti, vihārā aguttā honti.**They unlocked the doors with the keys and entered, but the dwellings were unprotected.*";
P_HTM[8140]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8141]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, yantakaṃ sūcikan”ti.**“I allow bolts.”*";
P_HTM[8142]="*Tena kho pana samayena vihārā tiṇacchadanā honti;**At that time the dwellings had roofs of straw.*";
P_HTM[8143]="*sītakāle sītā, uṇhakāle uṇhā.**When the weather was cold, they were cold, and when the weather was hot, they were hot.*";
P_HTM[8144]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8145]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ogumphetvā ullittāvalittaṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to firm up the structure and then to plaster it inside and outside.”*";
P_HTM[8146]="*Tena kho pana samayena vihārā avātapānakā honti acakkhussā duggandhā.**At that time the dwellings did not have windows. It was hard to see and the dwellings were smelly.*";
P_HTM[8147]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[8148]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tīṇi vātapānāni—**“I allow three kinds of windows:*";
P_HTM[8149]="*vedikāvātapānaṃ, jālavātapānaṃ, salākavātapānan”ti.**railing windows, lattice windows, and windows with bars.”*";
P_HTM[8150]="*Vātapānantarikāya kāḷakāpi vagguliyopi pavisanti.**Squirrels and bats entered the dwellings through the gaps in the windows.*";
P_HTM[8151]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8152]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, vātapānacakkalikan”ti.**“I allow a cloth-cover.”*";
P_HTM[8153]="*Cakkalikantarikāyapi kāḷakāpi vagguliyopi pavisanti.**The squirrels and bats entered in the gaps around the cloth cover.*";
P_HTM[8154]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8155]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, vātapānakavāṭakaṃ vātapānabhisikan”ti.**“I allow window shutters.”*";
P_HTM[8156]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū chamāyaṃ sayanti.**At that time the monks lay down on the ground.*";
P_HTM[8157]="*Gattānipi cīvarānipi paṃsukitāni honti.**They became dirty, as did their robes.*";
P_HTM[8158]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8159]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tiṇasanthārakan”ti.**“I allow straw mats.”*";
P_HTM[8160]="*Tiṇasanthārako undūrehipi upacikāhipi khajjati.**The straw mats were eaten by rats and termites.*";
P_HTM[8161]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8162]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, miḍḍhin”ti.**“I allow a bench.”*";
P_HTM[8163]="*Miḍḍhiyā gattāni dukkhā honti.**It was painful to lie on the bench.*";
P_HTM[8164]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8165]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bidalamañcakan”ti.**“I allow a wicker bed.”*";
P_HTM[8166]="*2. Mañcapīṭhādianujānana**1.2 The allowance for beds and benches*";
P_HTM[8167]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa sosāniko masārako mañco uppanno hoti.**Soon afterwards the Sangha was given, from a charnel ground, various kinds of beds with legs and frame.*";
P_HTM[8168]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[8169]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, masārakaṃ mañcan”ti.**“I allow the various kinds of beds with legs and frame.”*";
P_HTM[8170]="*Masārakaṃ pīṭhaṃ uppannaṃ hoti.**The Sangha was given various kinds of benches with legs and frame.*";
P_HTM[8171]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8172]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, masārakaṃ pīṭhan”ti.**“I allow the various kinds of benches with legs and frame.”*";
P_HTM[8173]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa sosāniko bundikābaddho mañco uppanno hoti.* **";
P_HTM[8174]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8175]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bundikābaddhaṃ mañcan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8176]="*Bundikābaddhaṃ pīṭhaṃ uppannaṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[8177]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8178]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bundikābaddhaṃ pīṭhan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8179]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa sosāniko kuḷīrapādako mañco uppanno hoti.**The Sangha was given, from a charnel ground, a bed with angular legs.*";
P_HTM[8180]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8181]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kuḷīrapādakaṃ mañcan”ti.**“I allow beds with angular legs.”*";
P_HTM[8182]="*Kuḷīrapādakaṃ pīṭhaṃ uppannaṃ hoti.**The Sangha was given a bench with angular legs.*";
P_HTM[8183]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8184]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kuḷīrapādakaṃ pīṭhan”ti.**“I allow benches with angular legs.”*";
P_HTM[8185]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa sosāniko āhaccapādako mañco uppanno hoti.**The Sangha was given, from a charnel ground, a bed with detachable legs.*";
P_HTM[8186]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8187]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, āhaccapādakaṃ mañcan”ti.**“I allow beds with detachable legs.”*";
P_HTM[8188]="*Āhaccapādakaṃ pīṭhaṃ uppannaṃ hoti.**The Sangha was given a bench with detachable legs.*";
P_HTM[8189]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8190]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, āhaccapādakaṃ pīṭhan”ti.**“I allow benches with detachable legs.”*";
P_HTM[8191]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa āsandiko uppanno hoti.**The Sangha was given a square bench.*";
P_HTM[8192]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8193]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, āsandikan”ti.**“I allow square benches.”*";
P_HTM[8194]="*Uccako āsandiko uppanno hoti.**The Sangha was given a tall square bench.*";
P_HTM[8195]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8196]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, uccakampi āsandikan”ti.**“I also allow tall square benches.”*";
P_HTM[8197]="*Sattaṅgo uppanno hoti.**The Sangha was given a sofa.*";
P_HTM[8198]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8199]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, sattaṅgan”ti.**“I allow sofas.”*";
P_HTM[8200]="*Uccako sattaṅgo uppanno hoti.**The Sangha was given a high sofa.*";
P_HTM[8201]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8202]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, uccakampi sattaṅgan”ti.**“I also allow high sofas.”*";
P_HTM[8203]="*Bhaddapīṭhaṃ uppannaṃ hoti.**The Sangha was given a cane bench.*";
P_HTM[8204]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8205]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhaddapīṭhan”ti.**“I allow cane benches.”*";
P_HTM[8206]="*Pīṭhikā uppannā hoti.**The Sangha was given a small bench bound with cloth.*";
P_HTM[8207]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8208]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pīṭhikan”ti.**“I allow small benches bound with cloth.”*";
P_HTM[8209]="*Eḷakapādakaṃ pīṭhaṃ uppannaṃ hoti.**The Sangha was given a bench with ram-like legs.*";
P_HTM[8210]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8211]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, eḷakapādakaṃ pīṭhan”ti.**“I allow benches with ram-like legs.”*";
P_HTM[8212]="*Āmalakavaṭṭikaṃ pīṭhaṃ uppannaṃ hoti.**The Sangha was given a bench with many legs.*";
P_HTM[8213]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8214]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, āmalakavaṭṭikaṃ pīṭhan”ti.**“I allow benches with many legs.”*";
P_HTM[8215]="*Phalakaṃ uppannaṃ hoti.**The Sangha was given a plank as a bench.*";
P_HTM[8216]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8217]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, phalakan”ti.**“I allow plank benches.”*";
P_HTM[8218]="*Kocchaṃ uppannaṃ hoti.**The Sangha was given a stool.*";
P_HTM[8219]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8220]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kocchan”ti.**“I allow stools.”*";
P_HTM[8221]="*Palālapīṭhaṃ uppannaṃ hoti.**The Sangha was given a bench made of straw.*";
P_HTM[8222]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8223]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, palālapīṭhan”ti.**“I allow benches made of straw.”*";
P_HTM[8224]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū ucce mañce sayanti.**At that time the monks from the group of six lay down on high beds.*";
P_HTM[8225]="*Manussā vihāracārikaṃ āhiṇḍantā passitvā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**When people walking about the dwellings saw this, they complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[8226]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[8227]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[8228]="*“Na, bhikkhave, ucce mañce sayitabbaṃ.**“You should not lie down on high beds.*";
P_HTM[8229]="*Yo sayeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[8230]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu nīce mañce sayanto ahinā daṭṭho hoti.**Soon afterwards a monk was bitten by a snake while lying on a low bed.*";
P_HTM[8231]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8232]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, mañcapaṭipādakan”ti.**“I allow bed supports.”*";
P_HTM[8233]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū ucce mañcapaṭipādake dhārenti, saha mañcapaṭipādakehi pavedhenti.**The monks from the group of six used high bed supports, and they then made the bed shake.*";
P_HTM[8234]="*Manussā vihāracārikaṃ āhiṇḍantā passitvā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**When people walking about the dwellings saw this, they complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[8235]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[8236]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8237]="*“Na, bhikkhave, uccā mañcapaṭipādakā dhāretabbā.**“You should not use high bed supports.*";
P_HTM[8238]="*Yo dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8239]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, aṭṭhaṅgulaparamaṃ mañcapaṭipādakan”ti.**I allow bed supports that are eight standard fingerbreadths at the most.”*";
P_HTM[8240]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa suttaṃ uppannaṃ hoti.**The Sangha was given string.*";
P_HTM[8241]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8242]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, suttaṃ mañcaṃ veṭhetun”ti.**“I allow you to wrap the beds with string.”*";
P_HTM[8243]="*Aṅgāni bahusuttaṃ pariyādiyanti.**The limbs of the bed took up a lot of string.*";
P_HTM[8244]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8245]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, aṅge vijjhitvā aṭṭhapadakaṃ veṭhetun”ti.**“I allow you to perforate the limbs and wrap with a cross-weaving.”*";
P_HTM[8246]="*Coḷakaṃ uppannaṃ hoti.**The Sangha was given a cloth.*";
P_HTM[8247]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8248]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cimilikaṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to make a mat underlay.”*";
P_HTM[8249]="*Tūlikā uppannā hoti.**The Sangha was given a cotton-down quilt.*";
P_HTM[8250]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8251]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, vijaṭetvā bibbohanaṃ kātuṃ.**“I allow you to remove the cotton down and make pillows.*";
P_HTM[8252]="*Tīṇi tūlāni—**There are three kinds of cotton down:*";
P_HTM[8253]="*rukkhatūlaṃ, latātūlaṃ, poṭakitūlan”ti.**cotton down from trees, cotton down from creepers, and cotton down from grass.”*";
P_HTM[8254]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū addhakāyikāni bibbohanāni dhārenti.**The monks from the group of six used large pillows, half the size of the body.*";
P_HTM[8255]="*Manussā vihāracārikaṃ āhiṇḍantā passitvā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**When people walking about the dwellings saw this, they complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[8256]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[8257]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8258]="*“Na, bhikkhave, aḍḍhakāyikāni bibbohanāni dhāretabbāni.**“You should not use large pillows, half the size of the body.*";
P_HTM[8259]="*Yo dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8260]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, sīsappamāṇaṃ bibbohanaṃ kātun”ti.**I allow you to make pillows the size of the head.”*";
P_HTM[8261]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājagahe giraggasamajjo hoti.**On one occasion in Rājagaha there was a hilltop fair.*";
P_HTM[8262]="*Manussā mahāmattānaṃ atthāya bhisiyo paṭiyādenti—**People prepared mattresses for the government officials:*";
P_HTM[8263]="*uṇṇabhisiṃ, coḷabhisiṃ, vākabhisiṃ, tiṇabhisiṃ, paṇṇabhisiṃ.**mattresses stuffed with wool, cloth, bark, grass, or leaves.*";
P_HTM[8264]="*Te vītivatte samajje chaviṃ uppāṭetvā haranti.**When the fair was over, they removed the covers and took them away.*";
P_HTM[8265]="*Addasāsuṃ kho bhikkhū samajjaṭṭhāne bahuṃ uṇṇampi coḷakampi vākampi tiṇampi paṇṇampi chaṭṭitaṃ.**The monks saw a large quantity of wool, cloth, bark, grass, and leaves abandoned on the ground.*";
P_HTM[8266]="*Disvāna bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[8267]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pañca bhisiyo—**“I allow you five kinds of mattresses:*";
P_HTM[8268]="*uṇṇabhisiṃ, coḷabhisiṃ, vākabhisiṃ, tiṇabhisiṃ, paṇṇabhisin”ti.**mattresses stuffed with wool, cloth, bark, grass, or leaves.”*";
P_HTM[8269]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa senāsanaparikkhārikaṃ dussaṃ uppannaṃ hoti.**The Sangha was given furniture cloth.*";
P_HTM[8270]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8271]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhisiṃ onandhitun”ti.**“I allow you to cover the mattresses.”*";
P_HTM[8272]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū mañcabhisiṃ pīṭhe santharanti, pīṭhabhisiṃ mañce santharanti.**The monks laid a bed mattress on a bench and a bench mattress on a bed.*";
P_HTM[8273]="*Bhisiyo paribhijjanti.**The mattresses split open.*";
P_HTM[8274]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8275]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, onaddhamañcaṃ onaddhapīṭhan”ti.**“I allow upholstered beds and upholstered benches.”*";
P_HTM[8276]="*Ullokaṃ akaritvā santharanti, heṭṭhato nipatanti …pe…**They put out a mattress without underlay. They sank down.*";
P_HTM[8277]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ullokaṃ karitvā santharitvā bhisiṃ onandhitun”ti.**“I allow you to put down an underlay, then to spread out a mattress, and then to cover it.”*";
P_HTM[8278]="*Chaviṃ uppāṭetvā haranti …pe…**The covers were removed and taken away.*";
P_HTM[8279]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, phositun”ti.**“I allow you to sprinkle them.”*";
P_HTM[8280]="*Harantiyeva …pe…**They were still taken away.*";
P_HTM[8281]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhattikamman”ti.**“I allow you to make multi-colored lines.”*";
P_HTM[8282]="*Harantiyeva …pe…**They were still taken away.*";
P_HTM[8283]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, hatthabhattikamman”ti.**“I allow you to make multi-colored lines by hand.”*";
P_HTM[8284]="*Harantiyeva …pe…**They were still taken away.*";
P_HTM[8285]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, hatthabhattin”ti.**“I allow multi-colored lines by hand.”*";
P_HTM[8286]="*3. Setavaṇṇādianujānana**1.3 The allowance for the color white, etc.*";
P_HTM[8287]="*Tena kho pana samayena titthiyānaṃ seyyāyo setavaṇṇā honti, kāḷavaṇṇakatā bhūmi, gerukaparikammakatā bhitti.**At that time the monastics of other religions had white beds, black floors, and red ocher walls.*";
P_HTM[8288]="*Bahū manussā seyyāpekkhakā gacchanti.**Many people went to see their beds.*";
P_HTM[8289]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8290]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, vihāre setavaṇṇaṃ kāḷavaṇṇaṃ gerukaparikamman”ti.**“I allow the colors white, black, and red ocher in the dwellings.”*";
P_HTM[8291]="*Tena kho pana samayena pharusāya bhittiyā setavaṇṇo na nipatati.**The white color did not adhere to a rough wall.*";
P_HTM[8292]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8293]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, thusapiṇḍaṃ datvā pāṇikāya paṭibāhetvā setavaṇṇaṃ nipātetun”ti.**“I allow you to smooth the wall by hand using balls of husk, and then apply the white color.”*";
P_HTM[8294]="*Setavaṇṇo anibandhanīyo hoti …pe…**The white color still did not adhere.*";
P_HTM[8295]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, saṇhamattikaṃ datvā pāṇikāya paṭibāhetvā setavaṇṇaṃ nipātetun”ti.**“I allow you to smooth the wall by hand using soft clay, and then apply the white color.”*";
P_HTM[8296]="*Setavaṇṇo anibandhanīyo hoti …pe…**The white color still did not adhere.*";
P_HTM[8297]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ikkāsaṃ piṭṭhamaddan”ti.**“I allow sap and flour paste.”*";
P_HTM[8298]="*Tena kho pana samayena pharusāya bhittiyā gerukā na nipatati.**The red ocher did not adhere to a rough wall.*";
P_HTM[8299]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8300]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, thusapiṇḍaṃ datvā pāṇikāya paṭibāhetvā gerukaṃ nipātetun”ti.**“I allow you to smooth the wall by hand using balls of husk, and then apply the red ocher.”*";
P_HTM[8301]="*Gerukā anibandhanīyā hoti …pe…**The red ocher still did not adhere.*";
P_HTM[8302]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kuṇḍakamattikaṃ datvā pāṇikāya paṭibāhetvā gerukaṃ nipātetun”ti.**“I allow you to smooth the wall by hand using clay mixed with bran, and then apply the red ocher.”*";
P_HTM[8303]="*Gerukā anibandhanīyā hoti …pe…**The red ocher still did not adhere.*";
P_HTM[8304]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, sāsapakuṭṭaṃ sitthatelakan”ti.**“I allow mustard powder and beeswax.”*";
P_HTM[8305]="*Accussannaṃ hoti …pe…**It was too thick.*";
P_HTM[8306]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, coḷakena paccuddharitun”ti.**“I allow you to wipe it off with a cloth.”*";
P_HTM[8307]="*Tena kho pana samayena pharusāya bhūmiyā kāḷavaṇṇo na nipatati.**The black color did not adhere to a rough floor.*";
P_HTM[8308]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8309]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, thusapiṇḍaṃ datvā pāṇikāya paṭibāhetvā kāḷavaṇṇaṃ nipātetun”ti.**“I allow you to smooth the floor by hand using balls of husk, and then apply the black color.”*";
P_HTM[8310]="*Kāḷavaṇṇo anibandhanīyo hoti …pe…**The black color still did not adhere.*";
P_HTM[8311]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gaṇḍumattikaṃ datvā pāṇikāya paṭibāhetvā kāḷavaṇṇaṃ nipātetun”ti.**“I allow you to smooth the floor by hand using excreted clay, and then apply the black color.”*";
P_HTM[8312]="*Kāḷavaṇṇo anibandhanīyo hoti …pe…**The black color still did not adhere.*";
P_HTM[8313]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ikkāsaṃ kasāvan”ti.**“I allow sap and bitter substances.”*";
P_HTM[8314]="*4. Paṭibhānacittapaṭikkhepa**1.4 The prohibition against pictures*";
P_HTM[8315]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū vihāre paṭibhānacittaṃ kārāpenti—**At that time the monks from the group of six had drawn pictures*";
P_HTM[8316]="*itthirūpakaṃ purisarūpakaṃ.**of women and men in a dwelling.*";
P_HTM[8317]="*Manussā vihāracārikaṃ āhiṇḍantā passitvā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**When people walking about the dwellings saw this, they complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[8318]="*“seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[8319]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[8320]="*“Na, bhikkhave, paṭibhānacittaṃ kārāpetabbaṃ—**“You should not draw pictures*";
P_HTM[8321]="*itthirūpakaṃ purisarūpakaṃ.**of women and men.*";
P_HTM[8322]="*Yo kārāpeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8323]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, mālākammaṃ latākammaṃ makaradantakaṃ pañcapaṭikan”ti.**I allow you to make a garland pattern, a creeper pattern, a shark-teeth pattern, and the fivefold pattern.”*";
P_HTM[8324]="*5. Iṭṭhakācayādianujānana**1.5 The allowance for foundations of bricks, etc.*";
P_HTM[8325]="*Tena kho pana samayena vihārā nīcavatthukā honti, udakena otthariyyanti.**At that time the dwellings were built on a low base. They were flooded.*";
P_HTM[8326]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8327]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, uccavatthukaṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to make a high base.”*";
P_HTM[8328]="*Cayo paripatati …pe…**The mound collapsed.*";
P_HTM[8329]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cinituṃ tayo caye—**“I allow you to construct three kinds of raised foundations:*";
P_HTM[8330]="*iṭṭhakācayaṃ, silācayaṃ, dārucayan”ti.**a raised foundation of brick, a raised foundation of stone, and a raised foundation of wood.”*";
P_HTM[8331]="*Ārohantā vihaññanti …pe…**It was difficult to get up to the dwelling.*";
P_HTM[8332]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tayo sopāne—**“I allow three kinds of stairs:*";
P_HTM[8333]="*iṭṭhakāsopānaṃ, silāsopānaṃ, dārusopānan”ti.**stairs of brick, stairs of stone, and stairs of wood.”*";
P_HTM[8334]="*Ārohantā paripatanti …pe…**People fell down while climbing the stairs.*";
P_HTM[8335]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ālambanabāhan”ti.**“I allow rails.”*";
P_HTM[8336]="*Tena kho pana samayena vihārā āḷakamandā honti.**At that time the dwellings were open to view.*";
P_HTM[8337]="*Bhikkhū hiriyanti nipajjituṃ.**The monks were embarrassed to lie down there.*";
P_HTM[8338]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8339]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tirokaraṇin”ti.**“I allow a curtain.”*";
P_HTM[8340]="*Tirokaraṇiṃ ukkhipitvā olokenti …pe…**People lifted them up and looked.*";
P_HTM[8341]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, aḍḍhakuṭṭakan”ti.**“I allow a half-wall.”*";
P_HTM[8342]="*Aḍḍhakuṭṭakā uparito olokenti …pe…**People looked over the half-wall.*";
P_HTM[8343]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tayo gabbhe—**“I allow three kinds of rooms:*";
P_HTM[8344]="*sivikāgabbhaṃ, nāḷikāgabbhaṃ, hammiyagabbhan”ti.**a rectangular room, a long room, and an upper room.”*";
P_HTM[8345]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū khuddake vihāre majjhe gabbhaṃ karonti.**On one occasion the monks made a room in the middle of a small dwelling.*";
P_HTM[8346]="*Upacāro na hoti.**There was no space around the room.*";
P_HTM[8347]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8348]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, khuddake vihāre ekamantaṃ gabbhaṃ kātuṃ, mahallake majjhe”ti.**“In a small dwelling you should make the room on the side, but in a large dwelling in the middle.”*";
P_HTM[8349]="*Tena kho pana samayena vihārassa kuṭṭapādo jīrati.**At that time the base of the wall belonging to a certain dwelling was deteriorating.*";
P_HTM[8350]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8351]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kulaṅkapādakan”ti.**“I allow a timber support.”*";
P_HTM[8352]="*Vihārassa kuṭṭo ovassati …pe…**It rained on the wall.*";
P_HTM[8353]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, parittāṇakiṭikaṃ uddasudhan”ti.**“I allow a protection screen and plastering.”*";
P_HTM[8354]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa bhikkhuno tiṇacchadanā ahi khandhe patati.**On one occasion a snake fell from the grass roof onto the shoulder of a certain monk.*";
P_HTM[8355]="*So bhīto vissaramakāsi.**Terrified, he screamed.*";
P_HTM[8356]="*Bhikkhū upadhāvitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocuṃ—**Other monks ran up to him and asked him*";
P_HTM[8357]="*“kissa tvaṃ, āvuso, vissaramakāsī”ti?**why he was screaming.*";
P_HTM[8358]="*Atha kho so bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**He told them.*";
P_HTM[8359]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8360]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, vitānan”ti.**“I allow a canopy.”*";
P_HTM[8361]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū mañcapādepi pīṭhapādepi thavikāyo laggenti.**At that time the monks hung bags from the legs of the beds and the benches.*";
P_HTM[8362]="*Undūrehipi upacikāhipi khajjanti.**Rats and termites ate them.*";
P_HTM[8363]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8364]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhittikhilaṃ nāgadantakan”ti.**“I allow wall pegs.”*";
P_HTM[8365]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū mañcepi pīṭhepi cīvaraṃ nikkhipanti.**At that time the monks lay their robes on their beds and benches.*";
P_HTM[8366]="*Cīvaraṃ paribhijji.**The robes tore.*";
P_HTM[8367]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8368]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, vihāre cīvaravaṃsaṃ cīvararajjun”ti.**“I allow bamboo robe racks and clotheslines in the dwellings.”*";
P_HTM[8369]="*Tena kho pana samayena vihārā anāḷindakā honti appaṭissaraṇā.**At that time the dwellings were not protected by porches.*";
P_HTM[8370]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8371]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, āḷindaṃ paghanaṃ pakuṭṭaṃ osārakan”ti.**“I allow porches, screened doorsteps, encircling corridors, and entrance roofs.”*";
P_HTM[8372]="*Āḷindā pākaṭā honti.**The porches were unenclosed.*";
P_HTM[8373]="*Bhikkhū hiriyanti nipajjituṃ …pe…**The monks were embarrassed to lie down there.*";
P_HTM[8374]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, saṃsaraṇakiṭikaṃ ugghāṭanakiṭikan”ti.**“I allow movable screens and removable screens.”*";
P_HTM[8375]="*6. Upaṭṭhānasālāanujānana**1.6 The allowance for an assembly hall*";
P_HTM[8376]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū ajjhokāse bhattavissaggaṃ karontā sītenapi uṇhenapi kilamanti.**At that time the monks were taking their meals outside. They were afflicted by cold and heat.*";
P_HTM[8377]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8378]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, upaṭṭhānasālan”ti.**“I allow an assembly hall.”*";
P_HTM[8379]="*Upaṭṭhānasālā nīcavatthukā hoti, udakena otthariyyati …pe…**The assembly hall was built on a low base. It was flooded.*";
P_HTM[8380]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, uccavatthukaṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to make a high base.”*";
P_HTM[8381]="*Cayo paripatati …pe…**The mound collapsed.*";
P_HTM[8382]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cinituṃ tayo caye—**“I allow you to construct three kinds of raised foundations:*";
P_HTM[8383]="*iṭṭhakācayaṃ, silācayaṃ, dārucayan”ti.**a raised foundation of brick, a raised foundation of stone, and a raised foundation of wood.”*";
P_HTM[8384]="*Ārohantā vihaññanti …pe…**It was difficult to get up to the assembly hall.*";
P_HTM[8385]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tayo sopāne—**“I allow three kinds of stairs:*";
P_HTM[8386]="*iṭṭhakāsopānaṃ, silāsopānaṃ, dārusopānan”ti.**stairs of brick, stairs of stone, and stairs of wood.”*";
P_HTM[8387]="*Ārohantā paripatanti …pe…**People fell down while climbing the stairs.*";
P_HTM[8388]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ālambanabāhan”ti.**“I allow rails.”*";
P_HTM[8389]="*Upaṭṭhānasālāya tiṇacuṇṇaṃ paripatati …pe…**Grass and dust fell into the assembly hall.*";
P_HTM[8390]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ogumphetvā ullittāvalittaṃ kātuṃ—**“I allow you to firm up the structure and then to plaster it inside and outside, including:*";
P_HTM[8391]="*setavaṇṇaṃ kāḷavaṇṇaṃ gerukaparikammaṃ mālākammaṃ latākammaṃ makaradantakaṃ pañcapaṭikaṃ cīvaravaṃsaṃ cīvararajjun”ti.**treating with white color, black color, and red ocher; making a garland pattern, a creeper pattern, a shark-teeth pattern, and the fivefold pattern; putting up a bamboo robe rack and a clothesline.”*";
P_HTM[8392]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū ajjhokāse chamāya cīvaraṃ pattharanti.**At that time the monks spread their robes on the ground outside.*";
P_HTM[8393]="*Cīvaraṃ paṃsukitaṃ hoti.**The robes became dirty.*";
P_HTM[8394]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8395]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ajjhokāse cīvaravaṃsaṃ cīvararajjun”ti.**“I allow a bamboo robe rack and a clothesline outside.”*";
P_HTM[8396]="*Pānīyaṃ otappati …pe…**The drinking water became warm.*";
P_HTM[8397]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pānīyasālaṃ pānīyamaṇḍapan”ti.**“I allow a shed and a roof-cover for the drinking water.”*";
P_HTM[8398]="*Pānīyasālā nīcavatthukā hoti, udakena otthariyyati …pe…**The drinking-water shed was built on a low base. It was flooded.*";
P_HTM[8399]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, uccavatthukaṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to make a high base.”*";
P_HTM[8400]="*Cayo paripatati …pe…**The mound collapsed.*";
P_HTM[8401]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cinituṃ tayo caye—**“I allow you to construct three kinds of raised foundations:*";
P_HTM[8402]="*iṭṭhakācayaṃ, silācayaṃ, dārucayan”ti.**a raised foundation of brick, a raised foundation of stone, and a raised foundation of wood.”*";
P_HTM[8403]="*Ārohantā vihaññanti …pe…**It was difficult to get up to the shed.*";
P_HTM[8404]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tayo sopāne—**“I allow three kinds of stairs:*";
P_HTM[8405]="*iṭṭhakāsopānaṃ, silāsopānaṃ, dārusopānan”ti.**stairs of brick, stairs of stone, and stairs of wood.”*";
P_HTM[8406]="*Ārohantā paripatanti …pe…**People fell down while climbing the stairs.*";
P_HTM[8407]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ālambanabāhan”ti.**“I allow rails.”*";
P_HTM[8408]="*Pānīyasālāya tiṇacuṇṇaṃ paripatati …pe…**Grass and dust fell into the drinking-water shed.*";
P_HTM[8409]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ogumphetvā ullittāvalittaṃ kātuṃ—**“I allow you to firm up the structure and then to plaster it inside and outside, including:*";
P_HTM[8410]="*setavaṇṇaṃ kāḷavaṇṇaṃ gerukaparikammaṃ mālākammaṃ latākammaṃ makaradantakaṃ pañcapaṭikaṃ cīvaravaṃsaṃ cīvararajjun”ti.**treating with white color, black color, and red ocher; making a garland pattern, a creeper pattern, a shark-teeth pattern, and the fivefold pattern; putting up a bamboo robe rack and a clothesline.”*";
P_HTM[8411]="*Pānīyabhājanaṃ na saṃvijjati …pe…**There was no vessel for the drinking water.*";
P_HTM[8412]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pānīyasaṅkhaṃ pānīyasarāvakan”ti.**“I allow a shell and a scoop.”*";
P_HTM[8413]="*7. Pākārādianujānana**1.7 The allowance for encircling walls, etc.*";
P_HTM[8414]="*Tena kho pana samayena vihārā aparikkhittā honti.**At that time the dwellings were unenclosed.*";
P_HTM[8415]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8416]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, parikkhipituṃ tayo pākāre—**“I allow you to make enclosures with three kinds of encircling walls:*";
P_HTM[8417]="*iṭṭhakāpākāraṃ, silāpākāraṃ, dārupākāran”ti.**a brick wall, a stone wall, and a wooden wall.”*";
P_HTM[8418]="*Koṭṭhako na hoti …pe…**There was no gateway.*";
P_HTM[8419]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, koṭṭhakan”ti.**“I allow a gateway.”*";
P_HTM[8420]="*Koṭṭhako nīcavatthuko hoti, udakena otthariyyati …pe…**They built the gateway on a low base. It was flooded.*";
P_HTM[8421]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, uccavatthukaṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to make a high base.”*";
P_HTM[8422]="*Koṭṭhakassa kavāṭaṃ na hoti …pe…**The gateway had no door.*";
P_HTM[8423]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kavāṭaṃ piṭṭhasaṅghāṭaṃ udukkhalikaṃ uttarapāsakaṃ aggaḷavaṭṭiṃ kapisīsakaṃ sūcikaṃ ghaṭikaṃ tāḷacchiddaṃ āviñchanacchiddaṃ āviñchanarajjun”ti.**“I allow a door, a door frame, a lower hinge, an upper hinge, a bolt-receiving post, a bolt socket, a bolt, an upper bolt, a keyhole, a door-pulling hole, and a door-pulling rope.”*";
P_HTM[8424]="*Koṭṭhake tiṇacuṇṇaṃ paripatati …pe…**Grass and dust fell into the gateway.*";
P_HTM[8425]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ogumphetvā ullittāvalittaṃ kātuṃ—**“I allow you to firm up the structure and then plaster it inside and outside, including:*";
P_HTM[8426]="*setavaṇṇaṃ kāḷavaṇṇaṃ gerukaparikammaṃ mālākammaṃ latākammaṃ makaradantakaṃ pañcapaṭikan”ti.**treating with white color, black color, and red ocher; making a garland pattern, a creeper pattern, a shark-teeth pattern, and the fivefold pattern.”*";
P_HTM[8427]="*Tena kho pana samayena pariveṇaṃ cikkhallaṃ hoti.**The precincts were muddy.*";
P_HTM[8428]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8429]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, marumbaṃ upakiritun”ti.**“I allow you to cover it with gravel.”*";
P_HTM[8430]="*Na pariyāpuṇanti …pe…**They were unable to do it.*";
P_HTM[8431]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, padarasilaṃ nikkhipitun”ti.**“I allow you to lay down paving stones.”*";
P_HTM[8432]="*Udakaṃ santiṭṭhati …pe…**The water remained.*";
P_HTM[8433]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, udakaniddhamanan”ti.**“I allow a water drain.”*";
P_HTM[8434]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū pariveṇe tahaṃ tahaṃ aggiṭṭhānaṃ karonti.**At that time the monks made fireplaces here and there in the precincts.*";
P_HTM[8435]="*Pariveṇaṃ uklāpaṃ hoti.**The precincts became dirty.*";
P_HTM[8436]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8437]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ekamantaṃ aggisālaṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to build a water-boiling shed out of the way.”*";
P_HTM[8438]="*Aggisālā nīcavatthukā hoti, udakena otthariyyati …pe…**They built the water-boiling shed on a low base. It was flooded.*";
P_HTM[8439]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, uccavatthukaṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to make a high base.”*";
P_HTM[8440]="*Cayo paripatati …pe…**The mound collapsed.*";
P_HTM[8441]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cinituṃ tayo caye—**“I allow you to construct three kinds of raised foundations:*";
P_HTM[8442]="*iṭṭhakācayaṃ, silācayaṃ, dārucayan”ti.**a raised foundation of brick, a raised foundation of stone, and a raised foundation of wood.”*";
P_HTM[8443]="*Ārohantā vihaññanti …pe…**It was difficult to get up to the water-boiling shed.*";
P_HTM[8444]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tayo sopāne—**“I allow three kinds of stairs:*";
P_HTM[8445]="*iṭṭhakāsopānaṃ, silāsopānaṃ, dārusopānan”ti.**stairs of brick, stairs of stone, and stairs of wood.”*";
P_HTM[8446]="*Ārohantā paripatanti …pe…**People fell down while climbing the stairs.*";
P_HTM[8447]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ālambanabāhan”ti.**“I allow rails.”*";
P_HTM[8448]="*Aggisālāya kavāṭaṃ na hoti …pe…**The water-boiling shed had no door.*";
P_HTM[8449]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kavāṭaṃ piṭṭhasaṅghāṭaṃ udukkhalikaṃ uttarapāsakaṃ aggaḷavaṭṭiṃ kapisīsakaṃ sūcikaṃ ghaṭikaṃ tāḷacchiddaṃ āviñchanacchiddaṃ āviñchanarajjun”ti.**“I allow a door, a door frame, a lower hinge, an upper hinge, a bolt-receiving post, a bolt socket, a bolt, an upper bolt, a keyhole, a door-pulling hole, and a door-pulling rope.”*";
P_HTM[8450]="*Aggisālāya tiṇacuṇṇaṃ paripatati …pe…**Grass and dust fell into the water-boiling shed.*";
P_HTM[8451]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ogumphetvā ullittāvalittaṃ kātuṃ—**“I allow you to firm up the structure and then to plaster it inside and outside, including:*";
P_HTM[8452]="*setavaṇṇaṃ kāḷavaṇṇaṃ gerukaparikammaṃ mālākammaṃ latākammaṃ makaradantakaṃ pañcapaṭikaṃ cīvaravaṃsaṃ cīvararajjun”ti.**treating with white color, black color, and red ocher; making a garland pattern, a creeper pattern, a shark-teeth pattern, and the fivefold pattern; putting up a bamboo robe rack and a clothesline.”*";
P_HTM[8453]="*8. Ārāmaparikkhepaanujānana**1.8 The allowance to enclose a monastery*";
P_HTM[8454]="*Tena kho pana samayena ārāmo aparikkhitto hoti.**At that time the monasteries were unenclosed.*";
P_HTM[8455]="*Ajakāpi pasukāpi uparope viheṭhenti.**Goats and domesticated animals harmed the saplings.*";
P_HTM[8456]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8457]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, parikkhipituṃ tayo vāṭe—**“I allow you to make three kinds of enclosures:*";
P_HTM[8458]="*veḷuvāṭaṃ, kaṇḍakavāṭaṃ, parikkhan”ti.**an enclosure made of bamboo, an enclosure made of thorny branches, and trenches.”*";
P_HTM[8459]="*Koṭṭhako na hoti.**There was no gateway.*";
P_HTM[8460]="*Tatheva ajakāpi pasukāpi uparope viheṭhenti …pe…**Goats and domesticated animals harmed the saplings just the same.*";
P_HTM[8461]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, koṭṭhakaṃ apesiṃ yamakakavāṭaṃ toraṇaṃ palighan”ti.**“I allow a gateway, a gate of wood and thorny branches, a double door, an arch, and a crossbar.”*";
P_HTM[8462]="*Koṭṭhake tiṇacuṇṇaṃ paripatati …pe…**Grass and dust fell into the gateway.*";
P_HTM[8463]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ogumphetvā ullittāvalittaṃ kātuṃ—**“I allow you to firm up the structure and then plaster it inside and outside, including:*";
P_HTM[8464]="*setavaṇṇaṃ kāḷavaṇṇaṃ gerukaparikammaṃ mālākammaṃ latākammaṃ makaradantakaṃ pañcapaṭikan”ti.**treating with white color, black color, and red ocher; making a garland pattern, a creeper pattern, a shark-teeth pattern, and the fivefold pattern.”*";
P_HTM[8465]="*Ārāmo cikkhallo hoti …pe…**The monasteries were muddy.*";
P_HTM[8466]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, marumbaṃ upakiritun”ti.**“I allow you to cover them with gravel.”*";
P_HTM[8467]="*Na pariyāpuṇanti …pe…**They were unable to do it.*";
P_HTM[8468]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, padarasilaṃ nikkhipitun”ti.**“I allow you to lay down paving stones.”*";
P_HTM[8469]="*Udakaṃ santiṭṭhati …pe…**The water remained.*";
P_HTM[8470]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, udakaniddhamanan”ti.**“I allow water drains.”*";
P_HTM[8471]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro saṅghassa atthāya sudhāmattikālepanaṃ pāsādaṃ kāretukāmo hoti.**On one occasion King Seniya Bimbisāra of Magadha wanted to build a stilt house smeared with clay plaster for the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[8472]="*Atha kho bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The monks thought,*";
P_HTM[8473]="*“kiṃ nu kho bhagavatā chadanaṃ anuññātaṃ, kiṃ ananuññātan”ti.**“Which roofing materials have been allowed by the Buddha and which have not?”*";
P_HTM[8474]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8475]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pañca chadanāni—**“I allow five kinds of roofing materials:*";
P_HTM[8476]="*iṭṭhakāchadanaṃ, silāchadanaṃ, sudhāchadanaṃ, tiṇacchadanaṃ, paṇṇacchadanan”ti.**tiles, slate, plaster, grass, and leaves.”*";
P_HTM[8477]="*Paṭhamabhāṇavāro niṭṭhito.**The first section for recitation is finished.*";
P_HTM[8478]="*1. Anāthapiṇḍikavatthu**2.1 The account of Anāthapiṇḍika*";
P_HTM[8479]="*Tena kho pana samayena anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati rājagahakassa seṭṭhissa bhaginipatiko hoti.**The householder Anāthapiṇḍika had a brother in law who was a wealthy merchant in Rājagaha.*";
P_HTM[8480]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati rājagahaṃ agamāsi kenacideva karaṇīyena.**On one occasion when Anāthapiṇḍika went to Rājagaha on business,*";
P_HTM[8481]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājagahakena seṭṭhinā svātanāya buddhappamukho saṅgho nimantito hoti.**that merchant had invited the Sangha headed by the Buddha for the meal on the following day.*";
P_HTM[8482]="*Atha kho rājagahako seṭṭhī dāse ca kammakāre ca āṇāpesi—**The merchant was telling his slaves and workers*";
P_HTM[8483]="*“tena hi, bhaṇe, kālasseva uṭṭhāya yāguyo pacatha, bhattāni pacatha, sūpāni sampādetha, uttaribhaṅgāni sampādethā”ti.**to get up early, to cook rice and rice porridge, and to prepare various kinds of curry.*";
P_HTM[8484]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa etadahosi—**Anāthapiṇḍika thought,*";
P_HTM[8485]="*“pubbe khvāyaṃ gahapati mayi āgate sabbakiccāni nikkhipitvā mamaññeva saddhiṃ paṭisammodati.**“When I’ve arrived here before, this householder put down all his business to greet me.*";
P_HTM[8486]="*Sodānāyaṃ vikkhittarūpo dāse ca kammakāre ca āṇāpesi—**But this time he’s all over the place,*";
P_HTM[8487]="*‘tena hi, bhaṇe, kālasseva uṭṭhāya yāguyo pacatha, bhattāni pacatha, sūpāni sampādetha, uttaribhaṅgāni sampādethā’ti.**telling his workers what to do.*";
P_HTM[8488]="*Kiṃ nu kho imassa gahapatissa āvāho vā bhavissati, vivāho vā bhavissati, mahāyañño vā paccupaṭṭhito, rājā vā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro nimantito svātanāya saddhiṃ balakāyenā”ti?**Is he preparing for a marriage or a great sacrifice, or has he invited King Seniya Bimbisāra of Magadha for a meal tomorrow, together with the army?”*";
P_HTM[8489]="*Atha kho rājagahako seṭṭhī dāse ca kammakāre ca āṇāpetvā yena anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā anāthapiṇḍikena gahapatinā saddhiṃ paṭisammoditvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**When the merchant was finished with telling his workers what to do, he went up to Anāthapiṇḍika, greeted him, and sat down.*";
P_HTM[8490]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho rājagahakaṃ seṭṭhiṃ anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati etadavoca—**Anāthapiṇḍika then told him what he had observed*";
P_HTM[8491]="*“pubbe kho tvaṃ, gahapati, mayi āgate sabbakiccāni nikkhipitvā mamaññeva saddhiṃ paṭisammodasi.* **";
P_HTM[8492]="*Sodāni tvaṃ vikkhittarūpo dāse ca kammakāre ca āṇāpesi—* **";
P_HTM[8493]="*‘tena hi, bhaṇe, kālasseva uṭṭhāya yāguyo pacatha, bhattāni pacatha, sūpāni sampādetha, uttaribhaṅgāni sampādethā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[8494]="*Kiṃ nu kho te, gahapati, āvāho vā bhavissati, vivāho vā bhavissati, mahāyañño vā paccupaṭṭhito, rājā vā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro nimantito svātanāya saddhiṃ balakāyenā”ti?**and asked him what was happening.*";
P_HTM[8495]="*“Na me, gahapati, āvāho vā bhavissati, nāpi vivāho vā bhavissati, nāpi rājā vā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro nimantito svātanāya saddhiṃ balakāyena;**The merchant replied, “I’m not preparing for a marriage, nor have I invited King Seniya Bimbisāra of Magadha together with the army.*";
P_HTM[8496]="*api ca me mahāyañño paccupaṭṭhito;**But I’m preparing for a great sacrifice.*";
P_HTM[8497]="*svātanāya buddhappamukho saṅgho nimantito”ti.**I have invited the Sangha headed by the Buddha for a meal tomorrow.”*";
P_HTM[8498]="*“Buddhoti tvaṃ, gahapati, vadesī”ti?**“Did you say, ‘Buddha’?” —*";
P_HTM[8499]="*“Buddho tyāhaṃ, gahapati, vadāmī”ti.**“I did.” —*";
P_HTM[8500]="*“Buddhoti tvaṃ, gahapati, vadesī”ti?**“Did you say, ‘Buddha’?” —*";
P_HTM[8501]="*“Buddho tyāhaṃ, gahapati, vadāmī”ti.**“I did.” —*";
P_HTM[8502]="*“Buddhoti tvaṃ, gahapati, vadesī”ti?**“Did you say, ‘Buddha’?” —*";
P_HTM[8503]="*“Buddho tyāhaṃ, gahapati, vadāmī”ti.**“I did.”*";
P_HTM[8504]="*“Ghosopi kho eso, gahapati, dullabho lokasmiṃ yadidaṃ—**“It’s rare in the world*";
P_HTM[8505]="*buddho buddhoti.**to hear the word ‘Buddha’.*";
P_HTM[8506]="*Sakkā nu kho, gahapati, imaṃ kālaṃ taṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhan”ti?**Is it possible at this time to go and visit that Buddha, that fully awakened and perfected one?”*";
P_HTM[8507]="*“Akālo kho, gahapati, imaṃ kālaṃ taṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ.**“Now is the wrong time to visit the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[8508]="*Svedāni tvaṃ kālena taṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissasi arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhan”ti.**Tomorrow will be the right time.”*";
P_HTM[8509]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati—**Because he lay down thinking of the Buddha—*";
P_HTM[8510]="*svedānāhaṃ kālena taṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissāmi arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhanti—**“Tomorrow I will go and visit that Buddha, that fully awakened and perfected one!”—*";
P_HTM[8511]="*buddhagatāya satiyā nipajjitvā rattiyā sudaṃ tikkhattuṃ vuṭṭhāsi pabhātaṃ maññamāno.**he got up three times during the night thinking it was light.*";
P_HTM[8512]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati yena sivakadvāraṃ tenupasaṅkami.**Anāthapiṇḍika then went to the Sivaka gate,*";
P_HTM[8513]="*Amanussā dvāraṃ vivariṃsu.**and the gate was opened by spirits.*";
P_HTM[8514]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa nagaramhā nikkhantassa āloko antaradhāyi, andhakāro pāturahosi, bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃso udapādi;**Then, as he was leaving town, the light disappeared and it was dark. He was paralyzed with fear, with goosebumps all over,*";
P_HTM[8515]="*tatova puna nivattitukāmo ahosi.**and he wanted to turn back.*";
P_HTM[8516]="*Atha kho sivako yakkho antarahito saddamanussāvesi—**Just then the invisible spirit Sivaka proclaimed:*";
P_HTM[8517]="*“Sataṃ hatthī sataṃ assā,**“A hundred elephants, a hundred horses,*";
P_HTM[8518]="*Sataṃ assatarīrathā;**A hundred carriages drawn by mules,*";
P_HTM[8519]="*Sataṃ kaññāsahassāni,**A hundred thousand girls*";
P_HTM[8520]="*Āmukkamaṇikuṇḍalā;**Wearing jeweled earrings*";
P_HTM[8521]="*Ekassa padavītihārassa,**Are not worth a sixteenth part*";
P_HTM[8522]="*Kalaṃ nāgghanti soḷasiṃ.**Of a single step forward.*";
P_HTM[8523]="*Abhikkama gahapati abhikkama gahapati,**Go forward, householder, go forward!*";
P_HTM[8524]="*Abhikkantaṃ te seyyo no paṭikkantan”ti.**Going forward is better for you than going back.”*";
P_HTM[8525]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa andhakāro antaradhāyi, āloko pāturahosi.**The light returned, the darkness disappeared,*";
P_HTM[8526]="*Yaṃ ahosi bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃso so paṭippassambhi.**and his fear subsided.*";
P_HTM[8527]="*Dutiyampi kho …pe…**A second*";
P_HTM[8528]="*tatiyampi kho …**and a third time*";
P_HTM[8529]="*anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa āloko antaradhāyi, andhakāro pāturahosi, bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃso udapādi, tatova puna nivattitukāmo ahosi.**the light disappeared and he was paralyzed with fear,*";
P_HTM[8530]="*Tatiyampi kho sivako yakkho antarahito saddamanussāvesi—**upon which the spirit proclaimed the same verses.*";
P_HTM[8531]="*“Sataṃ hatthī sataṃ assā,* **";
P_HTM[8532]="*Sataṃ assatarīrathā;* **";
P_HTM[8533]="*Sataṃ kaññāsahassāni,* **";
P_HTM[8534]="*Āmukkamaṇikuṇḍalā;* **";
P_HTM[8535]="*Ekassa padavītihārassa,* **";
P_HTM[8536]="*Kalaṃ nāgghanti soḷasiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8537]="*Abhikkama gahapati abhikkama gahapati,* **";
P_HTM[8538]="*Abhikkantaṃ te seyyo no paṭikkantan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8539]="*Tatiyampi kho anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa andhakāro antaradhāyi, āloko pāturahosi, yaṃ ahosi bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃso, so paṭippassambhi.**And on both occasions the light returned, the darkness disappeared, and his fear subsided.*";
P_HTM[8540]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati yena sītavanaṃ tenupasaṅkami.**Anāthapiṇḍika then went to the Sītavana, the Cool Grove.*";
P_HTM[8541]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhāya ajjhokāse caṅkamati.**Just then the Buddha was doing walking meditation outside, having got up early in the morning.*";
P_HTM[8542]="*Addasā kho bhagavā anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**When the Buddha saw Anāthapiṇḍika coming,*";
P_HTM[8543]="*Disvāna caṅkamā orohitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**he left the walking path, sat down on the prepared seat,*";
P_HTM[8544]="*Nisajja kho bhagavā anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[8545]="*“ehi, sudattā”ti.**“Come, Sudatta.”*";
P_HTM[8546]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati—**Anāthapiṇḍika thought,*";
P_HTM[8547]="*“nāmena maṃ bhagavā ālapatī”ti—**“The Buddha is addressing me by name!”*";
P_HTM[8548]="*haṭṭho udaggo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato pādesu sirasā nipatitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and glad and joyful he went up to him, bowed down with his head at the Buddha’s feet, and said,*";
P_HTM[8549]="*“kacci, bhante, bhagavā sukhaṃ sayitthā”ti?**“Venerable Sir, I hope you have slept well.”*";
P_HTM[8550]="*“Sabbadā ve sukhaṃ seti,**“Indeed, he always sleeps well,*";
P_HTM[8551]="*brāhmaṇo parinibbuto;**The brahmin who is extinguished,*";
P_HTM[8552]="*Yo na limpati kāmesu,**Who’s not soiled among worldly pleasures,*";
P_HTM[8553]="*sītibhūto nirūpadhi.**But is cool and ownerless.*";
P_HTM[8554]="*Sabbā āsattiyo chetvā,**After cutting all attachments,*";
P_HTM[8555]="*vineyya hadaye daraṃ;**After removing distress from the heart,*";
P_HTM[8556]="*Upasanto sukhaṃ seti,**Calmed, he sleeps well,*";
P_HTM[8557]="*santiṃ pappuyya cetasā”ti.**Having attained peace of mind.”*";
P_HTM[8558]="*Atha kho bhagavā anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa anupubbiṃ kathaṃ kathesi, seyyathidaṃ—**The Buddha then gave him a progressive talk—*";
P_HTM[8559]="*dānakathaṃ sīlakathaṃ saggakathaṃ, kāmānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṅkilesaṃ, nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ pakāsesi.**on generosity, morality, and heaven; on the danger, degradation, and defilement of worldly pleasures; and he revealed the benefits of renunciation.*";
P_HTM[8560]="*Yadā bhagavā aññāsi anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ kallacittaṃ muducittaṃ vinīvaraṇacittaṃ udaggacittaṃ pasannacittaṃ, atha yā buddhānaṃ sāmukkaṃsikā dhammadesanā taṃ pakāsesi—**When the Buddha knew that his mind was ready, supple, without hindrances, joyful, and confident, he revealed the teaching unique to the Buddhas:*";
P_HTM[8561]="*dukkhaṃ, samudayaṃ, nirodhaṃ, maggaṃ.**suffering, its origin, its end, and the path.*";
P_HTM[8562]="*Seyyathāpi nāma suddhaṃ vatthaṃ apagatakāḷakaṃ sammadeva rajanaṃ paṭiggaṇheyya;**And just as a clean and stainless cloth absorbs dye properly,*";
P_HTM[8563]="*evameva anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa tasmiṃyeva āsane virajaṃ vītamalaṃ dhammacakkhuṃ udapādi—**so too, while he was sitting right there, Anāthapiṇḍika experienced the stainless vision of the Truth:*";
P_HTM[8564]="*“yaṃ kiñci samudayadhammaṃ sabbaṃ taṃ nirodhadhamman”ti.**“Anything that has a beginning has an end.”*";
P_HTM[8565]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati diṭṭhadhammo pattadhammo viditadhammo pariyogāḷhadhammo tiṇṇavicikiccho vigatakathaṅkatho vesārajjappatto aparappaccayo satthusāsane bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**He had seen the Truth, had reached, understood, and penetrated it. He had gone beyond doubt and uncertainty, had attained to confidence, and had become independent of others in the Teacher’s instruction. He then said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[8566]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante.**“Wonderful, Sir, wonderful!*";
P_HTM[8567]="*Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya—**Just as one might set upright what had been overturned, or reveal what was hidden, or show the way to one who was lost, or bring a lamp into the darkness*";
P_HTM[8568]="*‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti;**so that one with eyes might see what’s there—*";
P_HTM[8569]="*evamevaṃ bhagavatā anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**just so has the Buddha made the Teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[8570]="*Esāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi, dhammañca, bhikkhusaṅghañca.**I go for refuge to the Buddha, the Teaching, and the Sangha of monks.*";
P_HTM[8571]="*Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gataṃ.**Please accept me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.*";
P_HTM[8572]="*Adhivāsetu ca me, bhante, bhagavā svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghenā”ti.**And please accept tomorrow’s meal from me together with the Sangha of monks.”*";
P_HTM[8573]="*Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena.**The Buddha consented by remaining silent.*";
P_HTM[8574]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**Knowing that the Buddha had consented, Anāthapiṇḍika got up from his seat, bowed down, circumambulated the Buddha with his right side toward him, and left.*";
P_HTM[8575]="*Assosi kho rājagahako seṭṭhī—**The merchant heard*";
P_HTM[8576]="*“anāthapiṇḍikena kira gahapatinā svātanāya buddhappamukho saṅgho nimantito”ti.**that Anāthapiṇḍika had invited the Sangha headed by the Buddha for the meal on the following day.*";
P_HTM[8577]="*Atha kho rājagahako seṭṭhī anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca—**And he said to Anāthapiṇḍika,*";
P_HTM[8578]="*“tayā kira, gahapati, svātanāya buddhappamukho saṅgho nimantito.**“You have invited the Sangha headed by the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[8579]="*Tvañcāsi āgantuko.**but you have just arrived here.*";
P_HTM[8580]="*Demi te, gahapati, veyyāyikaṃ yena tvaṃ buddhappamukhassa saṅghassa bhattaṃ kareyyāsī”ti.**I will give you the means to make a meal for them.”*";
P_HTM[8581]="*“Alaṃ, gahapati, atthi me veyyāyikaṃ yenāhaṃ buddhappamukhassa saṅghassa bhattaṃ karissāmī”ti.**“There’s no need. I have the necessary means.”*";
P_HTM[8582]="*Assosi kho rājagahako negamo—**The householder association of Rājagaha heard*";
P_HTM[8583]="*“anāthapiṇḍikena kira gahapatinā svātanāya buddhappamukho saṅgho nimantito”ti.**that Anāthapiṇḍika had invited the Sangha headed by the Buddha for a meal on the following day.*";
P_HTM[8584]="*Atha kho rājagahako negamo anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca—**And they said to Anāthapiṇḍika,*";
P_HTM[8585]="*“tayā kira, gahapati, svātanāya buddhappamukho saṅgho nimantito.**“You have invited the Sangha headed by the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[8586]="*Tvañcāsi āgantuko.**but you have just arrived here.*";
P_HTM[8587]="*Demi te, gahapati, veyyāyikaṃ yena tvaṃ buddhappamukhassa saṅghassa bhattaṃ kareyyāsī”ti.**We’ll give you the means to make a meal for them.”*";
P_HTM[8588]="*“Alaṃ, ayya;**“There’s no need, sirs.*";
P_HTM[8589]="*atthi me veyyāyikaṃ yenāhaṃ buddhappamukhassa saṅghassa bhattaṃ karissāmī”ti.**I have the necessary means.”*";
P_HTM[8590]="*Assosi kho rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro—**King Seniya Bimbisāra of Magadha heard*";
P_HTM[8591]="*“anāthapiṇḍikena kira gahapatinā svātanāya buddhappamukho saṅgho nimantito”ti.**that Anāthapiṇḍika had invited the Sangha headed by the Buddha for a meal on the following day.*";
P_HTM[8592]="*Atha kho rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca—**And he said to Anāthapiṇḍika,*";
P_HTM[8593]="*“tayā kira, gahapati, svātanāya buddhappamukho saṅgho nimantito.**“You have invited the Sangha headed by the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[8594]="*Tvañcāsi āgantuko.**but you have just arrived here.*";
P_HTM[8595]="*Demi te, gahapati, veyyāyikaṃ yena tvaṃ buddhappamukhassa saṅghassa bhattaṃ kareyyāsī”ti.**I will give you the means to make a meal for them.”*";
P_HTM[8596]="*“Alaṃ, deva;**“There’s no need, sir.*";
P_HTM[8597]="*atthi me veyyāyikaṃ yenāhaṃ buddhappamukhassa saṅghassa bhattaṃ karissāmī”ti.**I have the necessary means.”*";
P_HTM[8598]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati tassā rattiyā accayena rājagahakassa seṭṭhissa nivesane paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā bhagavato kālaṃ ārocāpesi—**The following morning, in that wealthy merchant’s house, Anāthapiṇḍika had various kinds of fine food prepared. He then had the Buddha informed*";
P_HTM[8599]="*“kālo, bhante, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan”ti.**that the meal was ready.*";
P_HTM[8600]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena rājagahakassa seṭṭhissa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghena.**The Buddha robed up, took his bowl and robe, and went to that merchant’s house, where he sat down on the prepared seat together with the Sangha of monks.*";
P_HTM[8601]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati buddhappamukhaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappetvā sampavāretvā, bhagavantaṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ, ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Anāthapiṇḍika then personally served the various kinds of fine food to the Sangha of monks headed by the Buddha. When the Buddha had finished his meal and had washed his hands and bowl, he sat down to one side*";
P_HTM[8602]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[8603]="*“adhivāsetu me, bhante, bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ vassāvāsaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghenā”ti.**“Sir, please spend the rainy-season residence at Sāvatthī together with the Sangha of monks.”*";
P_HTM[8604]="*“Suññāgāre kho, gahapati, tathāgatā abhiramantī”ti.**“The Buddha delights in solitude, householder.”*";
P_HTM[8605]="*“Aññātaṃ, bhagavā, aññātaṃ, sugatā”ti.**“I understand, Sir, I understand!”*";
P_HTM[8606]="*Atha kho bhagavā anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi.**Then, after instructing, inspiring, and gladdening him with a teaching, the Buddha got up from his seat and left.*";
P_HTM[8607]="*Tena kho pana samayena anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati bahumitto hoti bahusahāyo ādeyyavāco.**After finishing his business in Rājagaha,*";
P_HTM[8608]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati rājagahe taṃ karaṇīyaṃ tīretvā yena sāvatthi tena pakkāmi.**Anāthapiṇḍika set out for Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[8609]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati antarāmagge manusse āṇāpesi—**Now at that time Anāthapiṇḍika had many friends and acquaintances who listened to him. On his way to Sāvatthī*";
P_HTM[8610]="*“ārāme, ayyā, karotha, vihāre patiṭṭhāpetha, dānāni paṭṭhapetha.**he told people to make monasteries, to build dwellings, and to prepare offerings:*";
P_HTM[8611]="*Buddho loke uppanno.**“There’s a Buddha in the world!*";
P_HTM[8612]="*So ca mayā bhagavā nimantito iminā maggena āgacchissatī”ti.**He’s been invited by me and will be traveling this way.”*";
P_HTM[8613]="*Atha kho te manussā anāthapiṇḍikena gahapatinā uyyojitā ārāme akaṃsu, vihāre patiṭṭhāpesuṃ, dānāni paṭṭhapesuṃ.**And those people did as Anāthapiṇḍika had urged them to do.*";
P_HTM[8614]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati sāvatthiṃ gantvā samantā sāvatthiṃ anuvilokesi—**After arriving at Sāvatthī, Anāthapiṇḍika searched all around town for a place for the Buddha to stay, thinking,*";
P_HTM[8615]="*“kattha nu kho bhagavā vihareyya?**“Where might the Buddha stay*";
P_HTM[8616]="*Yaṃ assa gāmato neva atidūre na accāsanne, gamanāgamanasampannaṃ, atthikānaṃ atthikānaṃ manussānaṃ abhikkamanīyaṃ, divā appākiṇṇaṃ, rattiṃ appasaddaṃ, appanigghosaṃ, vijanavātaṃ, manussarāhasseyyakaṃ, paṭisallānasāruppan”ti.**that’s neither too far from the village nor too close, that has good access roads, that’s easily accessible for people who seek him, that has few people during the day and is quiet at night, that’s free from chatter and offers solitude, that’s away from human habitation and suitable for seclusion?”*";
P_HTM[8617]="*Addasā kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati jetassa kumārassa uyyānaṃ—**Anāthapiṇḍika saw that Prince Jeta’s park*";
P_HTM[8618]="*gāmato neva atidūre na accāsanne, gamanāgamanasampannaṃ, atthikānaṃ atthikānaṃ manussānaṃ abhikkamanīyaṃ, divā appākiṇṇaṃ, rattiṃ appasaddaṃ, appanigghosaṃ, vijanavātaṃ, manussarāhasseyyakaṃ, paṭisallānasāruppaṃ.**had all these qualities.*";
P_HTM[8619]="*Disvāna yena jeto kumāro tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā jetaṃ kumāraṃ etadavoca—**He then went to Prince Jeta and said,*";
P_HTM[8620]="*“dehi me, ayyaputta, uyyānaṃ ārāmaṃ kātun”ti.**“Sir, give me your park to make a monastery.”*";
P_HTM[8621]="*“Adeyyo, gahapati, ārāmo api koṭisantharenā”ti.**“I won’t give it even if you cover the park with ten million coins.”*";
P_HTM[8622]="*“Gahito, ayyaputta, ārāmo”ti.**“It’s a deal!”*";
P_HTM[8623]="*“Na, gahapati, gahito ārāmo”ti.**“No it isn’t.”*";
P_HTM[8624]="*“Gahito na gahito”ti vohārike mahāmatte pucchiṃsu.**They then asked judges to decide on the matter.*";
P_HTM[8625]="*Mahāmattā evamāhaṃsu—**They said,*";
P_HTM[8626]="*“yato tayā, ayyaputta, aggho kato, gahito ārāmo”ti.**“Sir, since you gave a price, the park is sold.”*";
P_HTM[8627]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati sakaṭehi hiraññaṃ nibbāhāpetvā jetavanaṃ koṭisantharaṃ santharāpesi.**Anāthapiṇḍika then had gold coins brought out in carts and covered the Jeta Grove with ten million coins.*";
P_HTM[8628]="*Sakiṃ nīhaṭaṃ hiraññaṃ thokassa okāsassa koṭṭhakasāmantā nappahoti.**After one more load had been brought out, there was still a small area near the gateway that was not covered.*";
P_HTM[8629]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati manusse āṇāpesi—**Anāthapiṇḍika told his people,*";
P_HTM[8630]="*“gacchatha, bhaṇe, hiraññaṃ āharatha;**“Go and get more coins.*";
P_HTM[8631]="*imaṃ okāsaṃ santharissāmā”ti.**We’ll cover this area too.”*";
P_HTM[8632]="*Atha kho jetassa kumārassa etadahosi—**But Prince Jeta thought,*";
P_HTM[8633]="*“na kho idaṃ orakaṃ bhavissati, yathāyaṃ gahapati tāva bahuṃ hiraññaṃ pariccajatī”ti.**“It must be really worthwhile, seeing as he’s giving up so much money.”*";
P_HTM[8634]="*Anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca—**And he said to Anāthapiṇḍika,*";
P_HTM[8635]="*“alaṃ, gahapati;**“It’s enough;*";
P_HTM[8636]="*mā taṃ okāsaṃ santharāpesi.**don’t cover that area.*";
P_HTM[8637]="*Dehi me etaṃ okāsaṃ.**Let me keep that area.*";
P_HTM[8638]="*Mametaṃ dānaṃ bhavissatī”ti.**That will be my gift.”*";
P_HTM[8639]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati—**Anāthapiṇḍika thought,*";
P_HTM[8640]="*ayaṃ kho jeto kumāro abhiññāto ñātamanusso;**“Prince Jeta is a well-known person.*";
P_HTM[8641]="*mahatthiko kho pana evarūpānaṃ ñātamanussānaṃ imasmiṃ dhammavinaye pasādoti—**It’s very beneficial that such well-known people gain confidence in this spiritual path.”*";
P_HTM[8642]="*taṃ okāsaṃ jetassa kumārassa pādāsi.**And he granted that area to Prince Jeta.*";
P_HTM[8643]="*Atha kho jeto kumāro tasmiṃ okāse koṭṭhakaṃ māpesi.**Prince Jeta then had a gateway built at that place.*";
P_HTM[8644]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati jetavane vihāre kārāpesi, pariveṇāni kārāpesi, koṭṭhake kārāpesi, upaṭṭhānasālāyo kārāpesi, aggisālāyo kārāpesi, kappiyakuṭiyo kārāpesi, vaccakuṭiyo kārāpesi, caṅkame kārāpesi, caṅkamanasālāyo kārāpesi, udapāne kārāpesi, udapānasālāyo kārāpesi, jantāghare kārāpesi, jantāgharasālāyo kārāpesi, pokkharaṇiyo kārāpesi, maṇḍape kārāpesi.**Anāthapiṇḍika had dwellings build in the Jeta Grove, and precincts, gateways, assembly halls, water-boiling sheds, food-storage huts, restrooms, walking-meditation paths, indoor walking-meditation paths, wells, well houses, saunas, sauna sheds, ponds, and roof-covers.*";
P_HTM[8645]="*2. Navakammadāna**2.2 Putting in charge of building work*";
P_HTM[8646]="*Atha kho bhagavā rājagahe yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena vesālī tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**When the Buddha had stayed at Rājagaha for as long as he liked, he set out wandering toward Vesālī.*";
P_HTM[8647]="*Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena vesālī tadavasari.**When he eventually arrived,*";
P_HTM[8648]="*Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ.**he stayed, in the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood.*";
P_HTM[8649]="*Tena kho pana samayena manussā sakkaccaṃ navakammaṃ karonti.**At that time people were doing careful building work.*";
P_HTM[8650]="*Yepi bhikkhū navakammaṃ adhiṭṭhenti tepi sakkaccaṃ upaṭṭhenti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena.**And the monks who supervised the building work were respectfully supported with robes, almsfood, dwellings, and medicines.*";
P_HTM[8651]="*Atha kho aññatarassa daliddassa tunnavāyassa etadahosi—**Then a certain poor tailor thought,*";
P_HTM[8652]="*“na kho idaṃ orakaṃ bhavissati, yathayime manussā sakkaccaṃ navakammaṃ karonti;**“It must be really worthwhile, seeing as these people do such careful building work.*";
P_HTM[8653]="*yannūnāhampi navakammaṃ kareyyan”ti.**Why donʼt I too do building work?”*";
P_HTM[8654]="*Atha kho so daliddo tunnavāyo sāmaṃ cikkhallaṃ madditvā iṭṭhakāyo cinitvā kuṭṭaṃ uṭṭhāpesi.**He then made a mixture of mud, made bricks out of it, and built a wall.*";
P_HTM[8655]="*Tena akusalakena citā vaṅkā bhitti paripati.**But because of his lack of skill, the wall was not straight and it fell down.*";
P_HTM[8656]="*Dutiyampi kho …pe…**A second*";
P_HTM[8657]="*tatiyampi kho so daliddo tunnavāyo sāmaṃ cikkhallaṃ madditvā iṭṭhakāyo cinitvā kuṭṭaṃ uṭṭhāpesi.**and a third time the same thing happened.*";
P_HTM[8658]="*Tena akusalakena citā vaṅkā bhitti paripati.* **";
P_HTM[8659]="*Atha kho so daliddo tunnavāyo ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**He then complained and criticized the monks,*";
P_HTM[8660]="*“ye imesaṃ samaṇānaṃ sakyaputtiyānaṃ denti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ, te ime ovadanti anusāsanti, tesañca navakammaṃ adhiṭṭhenti.**“These Sakyan monastics teach and instruct only those who give them robes, almsfood, dwellings, and medicines. They only supervise their building work.*";
P_HTM[8661]="*Ahaṃ panamhi daliddo.**But since I’m poor,*";
P_HTM[8662]="*Na maṃ koci ovadati vā anusāsati vā navakammaṃ vā adhiṭṭhetī”ti.**nobody teaches, instructs, or supervises me.”*";
P_HTM[8663]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassa daliddassa tunnavāyassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa.**The monks heard the complaints of that poor tailor.*";
P_HTM[8664]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They informed the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[8665]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**who gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[8666]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, navakammaṃ dātuṃ.**“You should put a monk in charge of the building work.*";
P_HTM[8667]="*Navakammiko, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ussukkaṃ āpajjissati—**The monk in charge of building work should make an effort*";
P_HTM[8668]="*‘kinti nu kho vihāro khippaṃ pariyosānaṃ gaccheyyā’ti;**to complete the dwellings as quickly as possible,*";
P_HTM[8669]="*khaṇḍaṃ phullaṃ paṭisaṅkharissati.**and he should repair what is broken or damaged.*";
P_HTM[8670]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbaṃ.**And he is to be put in charge like this.*";
P_HTM[8671]="*Paṭhamaṃ bhikkhu yācitabbo, yācitvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**First a monk should be asked, and then a competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[8672]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[8673]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmassa gahapatino vihāraṃ itthannāmassa bhikkhuno navakammaṃ dadeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should put monk so-and-so in charge of the building work relating to the dwelling of householder so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[8674]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[8675]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[8676]="*Saṅgho itthannāmassa gahapatino vihāraṃ itthannāmassa bhikkhuno navakammaṃ deti.**The Sangha puts monk so-and-so in charge of the building work relating to the dwelling of householder so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[8677]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa gahapatino vihāraṃ itthannāmassa bhikkhuno navakammassa dānaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of putting monk so-and-so in charge of that building work should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[8678]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[8679]="*Dinno saṅghena itthannāmassa gahapatino vihāro itthannāmassa bhikkhuno navakammaṃ.**The Sangha has put monk so-and-so in charge of the building work relating to the dwelling of householder so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[8680]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[8681]="*3. Aggāsanādianujānana**2.3 The instruction on the best seat, etc.*";
P_HTM[8682]="*Atha kho bhagavā vesāliyaṃ yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena sāvatthi tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**When the Buddha had stayed at Vesālī for as long as he liked, he set out wandering toward Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[8683]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ antevāsikā bhikkhū buddhappamukhassa saṅghassa purato purato gantvā vihāre pariggaṇhanti, seyyāyo pariggaṇhanti—**On that occasion the monks who were the pupils of the monks from the group of six went ahead of the Sangha headed by the Buddha and took possession of dwellings and beds, thinking,*";
P_HTM[8684]="*“idaṃ amhākaṃ upajjhāyānaṃ bhavissati, idaṃ amhākaṃ ācariyānaṃ bhavissati, idaṃ amhākaṃ bhavissatī”ti.**“This will be for our preceptors and teachers, and also for ourselves.”*";
P_HTM[8685]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto buddhappamukhassa saṅghassa piṭṭhito piṭṭhito gantvā vihāresu pariggahitesu, seyyāsu pariggahitāsu, seyyaṃ alabhamāno aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle nisīdi.**Venerable Sāriputta followed behind the Sangha. Being unable to get a bed—the dwellings and beds having all been taken—he sat down at the foot of a tree.*";
P_HTM[8686]="*Atha kho bhagavā rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhāya ukkāsi.**After getting up early in the morning, the Buddha cleared his throat.*";
P_HTM[8687]="*Āyasmāpi sāriputto ukkāsi.**Sāriputta, too, cleared his throat.*";
P_HTM[8688]="*“Ko etthā”ti?**“Who is there?”*";
P_HTM[8689]="*“Ahaṃ, bhagavā, sāriputto”ti.**“It’s me, Venerable Sir, Sāriputta.”*";
P_HTM[8690]="*“Kissa tvaṃ, sāriputta, idha nisinno”ti?**“Why are you sitting here?”*";
P_HTM[8691]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**Sāriputta told the Buddha what had happened.*";
P_HTM[8692]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[8693]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ antevāsikā bhikkhū buddhappamukhassa saṅghassa purato purato gantvā vihāre pariggaṇhanti, seyyāyo pariggaṇhanti—**“Is it true, monks, that the monks who are the pupils of the monks from the group of six did this?”*";
P_HTM[8694]="*idaṃ amhākaṃ upajjhāyānaṃ bhavissati, idaṃ amhākaṃ ācariyānaṃ bhavissati, idaṃ amhākaṃ bhavissatī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[8695]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[8696]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[8697]="*kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā buddhappamukhassa saṅghassa purato purato gantvā vihāre pariggahessanti, seyyāyo pariggahessanti—**“How can they act like this?*";
P_HTM[8698]="*idaṃ amhākaṃ upajjhāyānaṃ bhavissati, idaṃ amhākaṃ ācariyānaṃ bhavissati, idaṃ amhākaṃ bhavissatīti.* **";
P_HTM[8699]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[8700]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[8701]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[8702]="*“ko, bhikkhave, arahati aggāsanaṃ aggodakaṃ aggapiṇḍan”ti?**“Monks, who deserves the best seat, the best water, and the best almsfood?”*";
P_HTM[8703]="*Ekacce bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—**Some monks said,*";
P_HTM[8704]="*“yo, bhagavā, khattiyakulā pabbajito so arahati aggāsanaṃ aggodakaṃ aggapiṇḍan”ti.**“Those who have gone forth from an aristocratic family deserve the best seat, water, and almsfood.”*";
P_HTM[8705]="*Ekacce bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—**Others said,*";
P_HTM[8706]="*“yo, bhagavā, brāhmaṇakulā pabbajito so arahati aggāsanaṃ aggodakaṃ aggapiṇḍan”ti.**“Those who have gone forth from a brahmin family deserve the best seat, water, and almsfood.”*";
P_HTM[8707]="*Ekacce bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—**Still others said,*";
P_HTM[8708]="*“yo, bhagavā, gahapatikulā pabbajito so arahati aggāsanaṃ aggodakaṃ aggapiṇḍan”ti.**“Those who have gone forth from a householder family deserve the best seat, water, and almsfood.”*";
P_HTM[8709]="*Ekacce bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—* **";
P_HTM[8710]="*“yo, bhagavā, suttantiko so arahati aggāsanaṃ aggodakaṃ aggapiṇḍan”ti.**Or, “The experts on the discourses deserve the best seat, water, and almsfood.”*";
P_HTM[8711]="*Ekacce bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—* **";
P_HTM[8712]="*“yo, bhagavā, vinayadharo so arahati aggāsanaṃ aggodakaṃ aggapiṇḍan”ti.**Or, “The experts on the Monastic Law deserve the best seat, water, and almsfood.”*";
P_HTM[8713]="*Ekacce bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—* **";
P_HTM[8714]="*“yo, bhagavā, dhammakathiko so arahati aggāsanaṃ aggodakaṃ aggapiṇḍan”ti.**Or, “The expounders of the Teaching deserve the best seat, water, and almsfood.”*";
P_HTM[8715]="*Ekacce bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—* **";
P_HTM[8716]="*“yo, bhagavā, paṭhamassa jhānassa lābhī so arahati aggāsanaṃ aggodakaṃ aggapiṇḍan”ti.**Or, “Those who obtain the first absorption deserve the best seat, water, and almsfood.”*";
P_HTM[8717]="*Ekacce bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—* **";
P_HTM[8718]="*“yo, bhagavā, dutiyassa jhānassa lābhī so arahati aggāsanaṃ aggodakaṃ aggapiṇḍan”ti.**Or, “Those who obtain the second absorption deserve the best seat, water, and almsfood.”*";
P_HTM[8719]="*Ekacce bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—* **";
P_HTM[8720]="*“yo, bhagavā, tatiyassa jhānassa lābhī so arahati aggāsanaṃ aggodakaṃ aggapiṇḍan”ti.**Or, “Those who obtain the third absorption deserve the best seat, water, and almsfood.”*";
P_HTM[8721]="*Ekacce bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—* **";
P_HTM[8722]="*“yo, bhagavā, catutthassa jhānassa lābhī so arahati aggāsanaṃ aggodakaṃ aggapiṇḍan”ti.**Or, “Those who obtain the fourth absorption deserve the best seat, water, and almsfood.”*";
P_HTM[8723]="*Ekacce bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—* **";
P_HTM[8724]="*“yo, bhagavā, sotāpanno so arahati aggāsanaṃ aggodakaṃ aggapiṇḍan”ti.**Or, “The stream-enterers deserve the best seat, water, and almsfood.”*";
P_HTM[8725]="*Ekacce bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—* **";
P_HTM[8726]="*“yo, bhagavā, sakadāgāmī …pe…**Or, “The once-returners deserve the best seat, water, and almsfood.”*";
P_HTM[8727]="*yo, bhagavā, anāgāmī …pe…**Or, “The nonreturners deserve the best seat, water, and almsfood.”*";
P_HTM[8728]="*yo, bhagavā, arahā so arahati aggāsanaṃ aggodakaṃ aggapiṇḍan”ti.**Or, “The perfected ones deserve the best seat, water, and almsfood.”*";
P_HTM[8729]="*Ekacce bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—* **";
P_HTM[8730]="*“yo, bhagavā, tevijjo so arahati aggāsanaṃ aggodakaṃ aggapiṇḍan”ti.**Or, “Those who have attained the three true insights deserve the best seat, water, and almsfood.”*";
P_HTM[8731]="*Ekacce bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—* **";
P_HTM[8732]="*“yo, bhagavā, chaḷabhiñño so arahati aggāsanaṃ aggodakaṃ aggapiṇḍan”ti.**Or, “Those who have attained the six direct knowledges deserve the best seat, water, and almsfood.”*";
P_HTM[8733]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi—**The Buddha then addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[8734]="*“bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, himavantapadese mahānigrodho ahosi.**“Once upon a time, monks, there was a great banyan tree on the slope of the Himalayas.*";
P_HTM[8735]="*Taṃ tayo sahāyā upanissāya vihariṃsu—**Three friends lived near it:*";
P_HTM[8736]="*tittiro ca, makkaṭo ca, hatthināgo ca.**a partridge, a monkey, and an elephant.*";
P_HTM[8737]="*Te aññamaññaṃ agāravā appatissā asabhāgavuttikā viharanti.**They were disrespectful, undeferential, and rude toward one another.*";
P_HTM[8738]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, tesaṃ sahāyānaṃ etadahosi—**They thought,*";
P_HTM[8739]="*‘aho nūna mayaṃ jāneyyāma yaṃ amhākaṃ jātiyā mahantataraṃ taṃ mayaṃ sakkareyyāma garuṃ kareyyāma māneyyāma pūjeyyāma, tassa ca mayaṃ ovāde tiṭṭheyyāmā’ti.**‘If only we knew which one of us was the oldest. We would honor, respect, and esteem him, and we would wait for his instructions.’*";
P_HTM[8740]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, tittiro ca makkaṭo ca hatthināgaṃ pucchiṃsu—**The partridge and the monkey then asked the elephant,*";
P_HTM[8741]="*‘tvaṃ, samma, kiṃ porāṇaṃ sarasī’ti?**‘What’s your first memory?’*";
P_HTM[8742]="*‘Yadāhaṃ, sammā, poto homi, imaṃ nigrodhaṃ antarā satthīnaṃ karitvā atikkamāmi, aggaṅkurakaṃ me udaraṃ chupati.**‘When I was a young, I stepped over this banyan tree, keeping it between my thighs, and the top shoots touched my belly.*";
P_HTM[8743]="*Imāhaṃ, sammā, porāṇaṃ sarāmī’ti.**That’s my first memory.’*";
P_HTM[8744]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, tittiro ca hatthināgo ca makkaṭaṃ pucchiṃsu—**The partridge and the elephant asked the monkey,*";
P_HTM[8745]="*‘tvaṃ, samma, kiṃ porāṇaṃ sarasī’ti?**‘What’s your first memory?’*";
P_HTM[8746]="*‘Yadāhaṃ, sammā, chāpo homi, chamāyaṃ nisīditvā imassa nigrodhassa aggaṅkurakaṃ khādāmi.**‘When I was a young, I sat on the ground and ate the top shoots of the banyan tree.*";
P_HTM[8747]="*Imāhaṃ, sammā, porāṇaṃ sarāmī’ti.**That’s my first memory.’*";
P_HTM[8748]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, makkaṭo ca hatthināgo ca tittiraṃ pucchiṃsu—**The monkey and the elephant asked the partridge,*";
P_HTM[8749]="*‘tvaṃ, samma, kiṃ porāṇaṃ sarasī’ti?**‘What’s your first memory?’*";
P_HTM[8750]="*‘Amukasmiṃ, sammā, okāse mahānigrodho ahosi.**‘In such and such a spot there was a great banyan tree.*";
P_HTM[8751]="*Tato ahaṃ phalaṃ bhakkhitvā imasmiṃ okāse vaccaṃ akāsiṃ;**I ate one of its fruits and defecated here.*";
P_HTM[8752]="*tassāyaṃ nigrodho jāto.**This banyan tree has grown from that.*";
P_HTM[8753]="*Tadāhaṃ, sammā, jātiyā mahantataro’ti.**Well then, I must be the oldest one.’*";
P_HTM[8754]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, makkaṭo ca hatthināgo ca tittiraṃ etadavocuṃ—**The monkey and the elephant said to the partridge,*";
P_HTM[8755]="*‘tvaṃ, samma, amhākaṃ jātiyā mahantataro.**‘You’re the oldest of us.*";
P_HTM[8756]="*Taṃ mayaṃ sakkarissāma garuṃ karissāma mānessāma pūjessāma, tuyhañca mayaṃ ovāde patiṭṭhissāmā’ti.**We will honor, respect, and esteem you, and we’ll wait for your instructions.’*";
P_HTM[8757]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, tittiro makkaṭañca hatthināgañca pañcasu sīlesu samādapesi, attanā ca pañcasu sīlesu samādāya vattati.**The partridge had the monkey and the elephant take the five precepts, and he also undertook them himself.*";
P_HTM[8758]="*Te aññamaññaṃ sagāravā sappatissā sabhāgavuttikā viharitvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjiṃsu.**They were respectful, deferential, and courteous toward one another. And when they died, they were reborn in a happy, heavenly destination.*";
P_HTM[8759]="*Evaṃ kho taṃ, bhikkhave, tittiriyaṃ nāma brahmacariyaṃ ahosi.**In this way the spiritual life called _tittiriya_ came to be.*";
P_HTM[8760]="*‘Ye vuḍḍhamapacāyanti,**Those who respect the seniors,*";
P_HTM[8761]="*narā dhammassa kovidā;**And who are learned in the Teaching,*";
P_HTM[8762]="*Diṭṭhe dhamme ca pāsaṃsā,**They are praised while still alive,*";
P_HTM[8763]="*samparāye ca suggatī’ti.**And then go to a good destination.*";
P_HTM[8764]="*Te hi nāma, bhikkhave, tiracchānagatā pāṇā aññamaññaṃ sagāravā sappatissā sabhāgavuttikā viharissanti.**“Even those animals, monks, were respectful, deferential, and courteous toward one another.*";
P_HTM[8765]="*Idha kho taṃ, bhikkhave, sobhetha yaṃ tumhe evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye pabbajitā samānā aññamaññaṃ agāravā appatissā asabhāgavuttikā vihareyyātha?**Having gone forth on this well-proclaimed spiritual path, will you look good if you are disrespectful, undeferential, and rude toward one another?*";
P_HTM[8766]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[8767]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[8768]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[8769]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, yathāvuḍḍhaṃ abhivādanaṃ, paccuṭṭhānaṃ, añjalikammaṃ, sāmīcikammaṃ, aggāsanaṃ, aggodakaṃ, aggapiṇḍaṃ.**“You should do these things according to seniority: bowing down, standing up, raising your joined palms, doing acts of respect, giving the best seat, giving the best water, and giving the best almsfood.*";
P_HTM[8770]="*Na ca, bhikkhave, saṅghikaṃ yathāvuḍḍhaṃ paṭibāhitabbaṃ.**But what belongs to the Sangha should not be reserved according to seniority.*";
P_HTM[8771]="*Yo paṭibāheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[8772]="*4. Avandiyādipuggala**2.4 Persons one should not pay respect to, etc.*";
P_HTM[8773]="*“Dasayime, bhikkhave, avandiyā—**“Monks, you should not pay respect to these ten kinds of persons:*";
P_HTM[8774]="*pure upasampannena pacchā upasampanno avandiyo, anupasampanno avandiyo, nānāsaṃvāsako vuḍḍhataro adhammavādī avandiyo, mātugāmo avandiyo, paṇḍako avandiyo, pārivāsiko avandiyo, mūlāyapaṭikassanāraho avandiyo, mānattāraho avandiyo, mānattacāriko avandiyo, abbhānāraho avandiyo.**one who has been given the full ordination after you; one who isn’t fully ordained; one who belongs to a different Buddhist sect who is senior to you, but who speaks contrary to the Teaching; a woman; a _paṇḍaka_; one who is on probation; one who deserves to be sent back to the beginning; one who deserves the trial period; one who is undertaking the trial period; or one who deserves rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[8775]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dasa avandiyā.* **";
P_HTM[8776]="*Tayome, bhikkhave, vandiyā—**You should pay respect to these three kinds of persons:*";
P_HTM[8777]="*pacchā upasampannena pure upasampanno vandiyo, nānāsaṃvāsako vuḍḍhataro dhammavādī vandiyo, sadevake bhikkhave loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya tathāgato arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vandiyo.**one who has been given the full ordination before you; one who belongs to a different Buddhist sect who is senior to you and who speaks in accordance with the Teaching; and in this world with its gods, lords of death, and supreme beings, in this society with its monastics and brahmins, its gods and humans, you should pay respect to the Buddha, perfected and fully awakened.”*";
P_HTM[8778]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo vandiyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8779]="*5. Āsanappaṭibāhanapaṭikkhepa**2.5 The prohibition against reserving seats*";
P_HTM[8780]="*Tena kho pana samayena manussā saṅghaṃ uddissa maṇḍape paṭiyādenti, santhare paṭiyādenti, okāse paṭiyādenti.**At that time people prepared roof-covers, mats, and places to stay for the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[8781]="*Chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ antevāsikā bhikkhū—**The monks who were the pupils of the monks from the group of six, thought,*";
P_HTM[8782]="*“saṅghikaññeva bhagavatā yathāvuḍḍhaṃ anuññātaṃ, no uddissakatan”ti buddhappamukhassa saṅghassa purato purato gantvā maṇḍapepi pariggaṇhanti, santharepi pariggaṇhanti, okāsepi pariggaṇhanti—**“The Buddha has instructed that what belongs to the Sangha should not be reserved according to seniority. But he’s given no such instruction about what has merely been prepared for the Sangha.” They then went ahead of the Sangha headed by the Buddha and took possession of roof-covers, mats, and places to stay, thinking,*";
P_HTM[8783]="*“idaṃ amhākaṃ upajjhāyānaṃ bhavissati, idaṃ amhākaṃ ācariyānaṃ bhavissati, idaṃ amhākaṃ bhavissatī”ti.**“This will be for our preceptors and teachers, and also for ourselves.”*";
P_HTM[8784]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto buddhappamukhassa saṅghassa piṭṭhito piṭṭhito gantvā maṇḍapesu pariggahitesu, santharesu pariggahitesu, okāsesu pariggahitesu, okāsaṃ alabhamāno aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle nisīdi.**Venerable Sāriputta followed behind the Sangha. Being unable to get a place to stay—the roof-covers, the mats, and the places to stay having all been taken—he sat down at the foot of a tree.*";
P_HTM[8785]="*Atha kho bhagavā rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhāya ukkāsi.**After getting up early in the morning, the Buddha cleared his throat.*";
P_HTM[8786]="*Āyasmāpi sāriputto ukkāsi.**Sāriputta, too, cleared his throat.*";
P_HTM[8787]="*“Ko etthā”ti?**“Who is there?”*";
P_HTM[8788]="*“Ahaṃ, bhagavā, sāriputto”ti.**“It’s me, Venerable Sir, Sāriputta.”*";
P_HTM[8789]="*“Kissa tvaṃ, sāriputta, idha nisinno”ti?**“Why are you sitting here?”*";
P_HTM[8790]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**Sāriputta told the Buddha what had happened.*";
P_HTM[8791]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[8792]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ antevāsikā bhikkhū—**“Is it true, monks, that the monks who are the pupils of the monks from the group of six did this?”*";
P_HTM[8793]="*‘saṅghikaññeva bhagavatā yathāvuḍḍhaṃ anuññātaṃ, no uddissakatan’ti buddhappamukhassa saṅghassa purato purato gantvā maṇḍape pariggaṇhanti, santhare pariggaṇhanti, okāse pariggaṇhanti—* **";
P_HTM[8794]="*idaṃ amhākaṃ upajjhāyānaṃ bhavissati, idaṃ amhākaṃ ācariyānaṃ bhavissati, idaṃ amhākaṃ bhavissatī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[8795]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[8796]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[8797]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[8798]="*“na, bhikkhave, uddissakatampi yathāvuḍḍhaṃ paṭibāhitabbaṃ.**“Even what has merely been prepared for the Sangha should not be reserved according to seniority.*";
P_HTM[8799]="*Yo paṭibāheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[8800]="*6. Gihivikataanujānana**2.6 The allowance for what belongs to a householder*";
P_HTM[8801]="*Tena kho pana samayena manussā bhattagge antaraghare uccāsayanamahāsayanāni paññapenti, seyyathidaṃ—**At that time people prepared high and luxurious resting places in the dining halls in inhabited areas, that is:*";
P_HTM[8802]="*āsandiṃ, pallaṅkaṃ, gonakaṃ, cittakaṃ, paṭikaṃ, paṭalikaṃ, tūlikaṃ, vikatikaṃ, uddalomiṃ, ekantalomiṃ, kaṭṭissaṃ, koseyyaṃ, kuttakaṃ, hatthattharaṃ, assattharaṃ, rathattharaṃ, ajinapaveṇiṃ, kadalimigapavarapaccattharaṇaṃ, sauttaracchadaṃ, ubhatolohitakūpadhānaṃ.**a high couch, a luxurious couch, a long-fleeced woolen rug, a multi-colored woolen rug, a white woolen rug, a red woolen rug, a cotton-down quilt, a woolen rug decorated with the images of predatory animals, a woolen rug with long fleece on one side, a woolen rug with long fleece on both sides, a sheet of silk embroidered with gems, a silken sheet, a woolen rug like a dancers’ rug, an elephant-back rug, a horse-back rug, a carriage-seat rug, a rug made of black antelope hide, an excellent rug made of _kadalī_-deer hide, a seat with a canopy, a seat with red cushions at each end.*";
P_HTM[8803]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nābhinisīdanti.**Being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not sit on them.*";
P_HTM[8804]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[8805]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ṭhapetvā tīṇi—**“Apart from*";
P_HTM[8806]="*āsandiṃ, pallaṅkaṃ, tūlikaṃ—**the high couch, the luxurious couch, and the cotton-down quilt,*";
P_HTM[8807]="*gihivikataṃ abhinisīdituṃ, na tveva abhinipajjitun”ti.**I allow you to sit down on what belongs to householders, but not to lie down on it.”*";
P_HTM[8808]="*Tena kho pana samayena manussā bhattagge antaraghare tūlonaddhaṃ mañcampi pīṭhampi paññapenti.**At that time people prepared beds and benches upholstered with cotton down in the dining halls in inhabited areas.*";
P_HTM[8809]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nābhinisīdanti.**Being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not sit on them.*";
P_HTM[8810]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[8811]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gihivikataṃ abhinisīdituṃ, na tveva abhinipajjitun”ti.**“I allow you to sit down on what belongs to householders, but not to lie down on it.”*";
P_HTM[8812]="*7. Jetavanavihārānumodanā**2.7 The expression of appreciation for the Jeta Grove dwellings*";
P_HTM[8813]="*Atha kho bhagavā anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena sāvatthi tadavasari.**Wandering on, the Buddha eventually arrived at Sāvatthī,*";
P_HTM[8814]="*Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**where he stayed in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Park.*";
P_HTM[8815]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Anāthapiṇḍika then went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[8816]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[8817]="*“adhivāsetu me, bhante, bhagavā svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghenā”ti.**“Venerable Sir, please accept tomorrow’s meal from me together with the Sangha of monks.”*";
P_HTM[8818]="*Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena.**The Buddha consented by remaining silent.*";
P_HTM[8819]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**Knowing that the Buddha had consented, Anāthapiṇḍika got up from his seat, bowed down, circumambulated the Buddha with his right side toward him, and left.*";
P_HTM[8820]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati tassā rattiyā accayena paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā bhagavato kālaṃ ārocāpesi—**The following morning Anāthapiṇḍika had various kinds of fine food prepared. He then had the Buddha informed*";
P_HTM[8821]="*“kālo, bhante, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan”ti.**that the meal was ready.*";
P_HTM[8822]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghena.**The Buddha robed up, took his bowl and robe, and went to Anāthapiṇḍika’s house, where he sat down on the prepared seat together with the Sangha of monks.*";
P_HTM[8823]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati buddhappamukhaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappetvā sampavāretvā, bhagavantaṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ, ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Anāthapiṇḍika then personally served various kinds of fine food to the Sangha of monks headed by the Buddha. When the Buddha had finished his meal and had washed his hands and bowl, Anāthapiṇḍika sat down to one side*";
P_HTM[8824]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[8825]="*“kathāhaṃ, bhante, jetavane paṭipajjāmī”ti?**“Sir, what should I do in regard to the Jeta Grove?”*";
P_HTM[8826]="*“Tena hi tvaṃ, gahapati, jetavanaṃ āgatānāgatassa cātuddisassa saṅghassa patiṭṭhapehī”ti.**“You should dedicate the Jeta Grove to the Sangha everywhere, present and future.”*";
P_HTM[8827]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati bhagavato paṭissutvā jetavanaṃ āgatānāgatassa cātuddisassa saṅghassa patiṭṭhāpesi.**“Yes.” And he did just that.*";
P_HTM[8828]="*Atha kho bhagavā anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ imāhi gāthāhi anumodi—**The Buddha then expressed his appreciation with these verses:*";
P_HTM[8829]="*“Sītaṃ uṇhaṃ paṭihanti,**“Cold and heat are kept away,*";
P_HTM[8830]="*tato vāḷamigāni ca;**And predatory animals too,*";
P_HTM[8831]="*Sarīsape ca makase,**And creeping animals and mosquitoes,*";
P_HTM[8832]="*sisire cāpi vuṭṭhiyo.**And also chill and rain.*";
P_HTM[8833]="*Tato vātātapo ghoro,**It keeps away the burning wind,*";
P_HTM[8834]="*sañjāto paṭihaññati;**That terrible thing that comes.*";
P_HTM[8835]="*Leṇatthañca sukhatthañca,**It’s for the sake of shelter and happiness,*";
P_HTM[8836]="*jhāyituñca vipassituṃ.**To attain absorption and to see clearly.*";
P_HTM[8837]="*Vihāradānaṃ saṅghassa,**Giving dwellings to the Sangha*";
P_HTM[8838]="*aggaṃ buddhena vaṇṇitaṃ;**Is praised as the best by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[8839]="*Tasmā hi paṇḍito poso,**Therefore the wise man,*";
P_HTM[8840]="*sampassaṃ atthamattano.**Seeing what is beneficial for himself,*";
P_HTM[8841]="*Vihāre kāraye ramme,**Should build delightful dwellings*";
P_HTM[8842]="*vāsayettha bahussute;**And have the learned stay there.*";
P_HTM[8843]="*Tesaṃ annañca pānañca,**Food, drink, cloth, and dwellings—*";
P_HTM[8844]="*vatthasenāsanāni ca.**With an inspired mind,*";
P_HTM[8845]="*Dadeyya ujubhūtesu,**He should give to them,*";
P_HTM[8846]="*Vippasannena cetasā;**The upright ones.*";
P_HTM[8847]="*Te tassa dhammaṃ desenti,**They will give him the Teaching*";
P_HTM[8848]="*Sabbadukkhāpanūdanaṃ;**For removing all suffering;*";
P_HTM[8849]="*Yaṃ so dhammaṃ idhaññāya,**And understanding this Teaching in this very life,*";
P_HTM[8850]="*Parinibbāti anāsavo”ti.**He attains extinguishment, free of corruptions.”*";
P_HTM[8851]="*Atha kho bhagavā anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ imāhi gāthāhi anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi.**The Buddha then got up from his seat and left.*";
P_HTM[8852]="*8. Āsanappaṭibāhanādi**2.8 Reservation of seats, etc.*";
P_HTM[8853]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa ājīvakasāvakassa mahāmattassa saṅghabhattaṃ hoti.**On one occasion a certain government official who was an Ājīvaka disciple was offering a meal to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[8854]="*Āyasmā upanando sakyaputto pacchā āgantvā vippakatabhojanaṃ ānantarikaṃ bhikkhuṃ vuṭṭhāpesi.**Arriving late, Venerable Upananda the Sakyan made the nearest monk get up before he had finished his meal.*";
P_HTM[8855]="*Bhattaggaṃ kolāhalaṃ ahosi.**There was an uproar in the dining hall.*";
P_HTM[8856]="*Atha kho so mahāmatto ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**The official complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[8857]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā pacchā āgantvā vippakatabhojanaṃ ānantarikaṃ bhikkhuṃ vuṭṭhāpessanti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics arrive late and make the nearest monk get up in the middle of his meal?*";
P_HTM[8858]="*Bhattaggaṃ kolāhalaṃ ahosi.**There was an uproar in the dining hall.*";
P_HTM[8859]="*Nanu nāma labbhā aññatrāpi nisinnena yāvadatthaṃ bhuñjitun”ti?**It’s impossible to eat as much as you like when you’re not seated.”*";
P_HTM[8860]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassa mahāmattassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa.**The monks heard the complaints of the official,*";
P_HTM[8861]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[8862]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto pacchā āgantvā vippakatabhojanaṃ ānantarikaṃ bhikkhuṃ vuṭṭhāpessati.**“How could Upananda act like this?”*";
P_HTM[8863]="*Bhattaggaṃ kolāhalaṃ ahosī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8864]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha what had happened.*";
P_HTM[8865]="*“Saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, pacchā āgantvā vippakatabhojanaṃ ānantarikaṃ bhikkhuṃ vuṭṭhāpesi, bhattaggaṃ kolāhalaṃ ahosī”ti?**“Is it true, Upananda, that you acted like this?”*";
P_HTM[8866]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[8867]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[8868]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, pacchā āgantvā vippakatabhojanaṃ ānantarikaṃ bhikkhuṃ vuṭṭhāpessasi?**“Foolish man, how can you act like this?*";
P_HTM[8869]="*Bhattaggaṃ kolāhalaṃ ahosi.* **";
P_HTM[8870]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[8871]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after rebuking him …*";
P_HTM[8872]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[8873]="*“na, bhikkhave, vippakatabhojano bhikkhu vuṭṭhāpetabbo.**“You should not make a monk get up who hasn’t finished his meal.*";
P_HTM[8874]="*Yo vuṭṭhāpeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8875]="*Sace vuṭṭhāpeti, pavārito ca hoti, ‘gaccha udakaṃ āharā’ti vattabbo.**If you’re asked to get up, and you have already refused an invitation to eat more, you should say, “Please, go and get some water.”*";
P_HTM[8876]="*Evañcetaṃ labhetha, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ.**If the other goes, all is well.*";
P_HTM[8877]="*No ce labhetha, sādhukaṃ sitthāni gilitvā vuḍḍhatarassa bhikkhuno āsanaṃ dātabbaṃ.**If not, you should properly swallow the mouthful and give the seat to the more senior monk.*";
P_HTM[8878]="*Na tvevāhaṃ, bhikkhave, kenaci pariyāyena vuḍḍhatarassa bhikkhuno āsanaṃ paṭibāhitabbanti vadāmi.**Under no circumstances should you block a more senior monk from a seat.*";
P_HTM[8879]="*Yo paṭibāheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassāti”.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[8880]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū gilāne bhikkhū vuṭṭhāpenti.**On one occasion the monks from the group of six asked the sick monks to get up.*";
P_HTM[8881]="*Gilānā evaṃ vadenti—**The sick monks said,*";
P_HTM[8882]="*“na mayaṃ, āvuso, sakkoma vuṭṭhātuṃ, gilānāmhā”ti.**“We’re not able to get up; we’re sick.”*";
P_HTM[8883]="*“Mayaṃ āyasmante vuṭṭhāpessāmā”ti pariggahetvā vuṭṭhāpetvā ṭhitake muñcanti.**Saying, “We’ll make the venerables get up,” they took hold of them, lifted them up, and then released them when they were standing.*";
P_HTM[8884]="*Gilānā mucchitā papatanti.**The sick monks fainted and collapsed.*";
P_HTM[8885]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8886]="*“Na, bhikkhave, gilāno vuṭṭhāpetabbo.**“You should not make the sick get up.*";
P_HTM[8887]="*Yo vuṭṭhāpeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[8888]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū—**The monks from the group of six took possession of the best beds, saying,*";
P_HTM[8889]="*“gilānā mayamhā avuṭṭhāpanīyā”ti varaseyyāyo palibuddhenti.**“We’re sick and no one can make us get up.”*";
P_HTM[8890]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8891]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānassa patirūpaṃ seyyaṃ dātun”ti.**“You should give suitable beds to those who are sick.”*";
P_HTM[8892]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū lesakappena senāsanaṃ paṭibāhanti.**The monks from the group of six used a pretext to reserve resting places.*";
P_HTM[8893]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8894]="*“Na, bhikkhave, lesakappena senāsanaṃ paṭibāhitabbaṃ.**“You should not use a pretext to reserve a resting place.*";
P_HTM[8895]="*Yo paṭibāheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[8896]="*Tena kho pana samayena sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū aññataraṃ paccantimaṃ mahāvihāraṃ paṭisaṅkharonti—**At that time the monks from the group of seventeen were repairing a large dwelling nearby,*";
P_HTM[8897]="*“idha mayaṃ vassaṃ vasissāmā”ti.**intending to stay there for the rainy season.*";
P_HTM[8898]="*Addasaṃsu kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū sattarasavaggiye bhikkhū vihāraṃ paṭisaṅkharonte.**The monks from the group of six saw this*";
P_HTM[8899]="*Disvāna evamāhaṃsu—**and said,*";
P_HTM[8900]="*“ime, āvuso, sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū vihāraṃ paṭisaṅkharonti.**“These monks from the group of seventeen are repairing a dwelling.*";
P_HTM[8901]="*Handa ne vuṭṭhāpessāmā”ti.**Let’s throw them out.”*";
P_HTM[8902]="*Ekacce evamāhaṃsu—**But some of them said,*";
P_HTM[8903]="*“āgamethāvuso, yāva paṭisaṅkharonti, paṭisaṅkhate vuṭṭhāpessāmā”ti.**“Let’s wait until they’ve finished repairing it.”*";
P_HTM[8904]="*Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū sattarasavaggiye bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—**Soon afterwards the monks from the group of six said to those from the group of seventeen,*";
P_HTM[8905]="*“uṭṭhethāvuso, amhākaṃ vihāro pāpuṇātī”ti.**“Leave, this dwelling is ours.”*";
P_HTM[8906]="*“Nanu, āvuso, paṭikacceva ācikkhitabbaṃ?**“Shouldn’t you have told us beforehand?*";
P_HTM[8907]="*Mayañcaññaṃ paṭisaṅkhareyyāmā”ti.**We would have repaired another one.”*";
P_HTM[8908]="*“Nanu, āvuso, saṅghiko vihāro”ti?**“Doesn’t this dwelling belong to the Sangha?”*";
P_HTM[8909]="*“Āmāvuso, saṅghiko vihāro”ti.**“Yes it does.”*";
P_HTM[8910]="*“Uṭṭhethāvuso, amhākaṃ vihāro pāpuṇātī”ti.**“Well then, leave; this dwelling is ours.”*";
P_HTM[8911]="*“Mahallako, āvuso, vihāro;**“The dwelling is large.*";
P_HTM[8912]="*tumhepi vasatha, mayampi vasissāmā”ti.**You can stay here and so can we.”*";
P_HTM[8913]="*“Uṭṭhethāvuso, amhākaṃ vihāro pāpuṇātī”ti kupitā anattamanā gīvāyaṃ gahetvā nikkaḍḍhanti.**But they said, “Leave, this dwelling is ours,” and they grabbed them by the neck and threw them out in anger.*";
P_HTM[8914]="*Te nikkaḍḍhiyamānā rodanti.**The monks from the group of seventeen cried.*";
P_HTM[8915]="*Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—**When other monks asked them why,*";
P_HTM[8916]="*“kissa tumhe, āvuso, rodathā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[8917]="*“Ime, āvuso, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kupitā anattamanā amhe saṅghikā vihārā nikkaḍḍhantī”ti.**they told them what had happened.*";
P_HTM[8918]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[8919]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kupitā anattamanā bhikkhū saṅghikā vihārā nikkaḍḍhissantī”ti.**“How can the monks from the group of six angrily throw other monks out of a dwelling belonging to the Sangha?”*";
P_HTM[8920]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[8921]="*“saccaṃ kira, tumhe bhikkhave, kupitā anattamanā saṅghikā vihārā bhikkhū nikkaḍḍhathā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[8922]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[8923]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[8924]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**and after giving a teaching, he addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[8925]="*“na, bhikkhave, kupitena anattamanena bhikkhu saṅghikā vihārā nikkaḍḍhitabbo.**“You should not, in anger, throw a monk out of a dwelling belonging to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[8926]="*Yo nikkaḍḍheyya, yathādhammo kāretabbo.**If you do, you should be dealt with according to the rule.*";
P_HTM[8927]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, senāsanaṃ gāhetun”ti.**You should allocate the dwellings.”*";
P_HTM[8928]="*9. Senāsanaggāhāpakasammuti**2.9 The appointment of allocators of dwellings*";
P_HTM[8929]="*Atha kho bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The monks thought,*";
P_HTM[8930]="*“kena nu kho senāsanaṃ gāhetabban”ti?**“Who should allocate the dwellings?”*";
P_HTM[8931]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[8932]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgataṃ bhikkhuṃ senāsanaggāhāpakaṃ sammannituṃ—**“You should appoint a monk who has five qualities as the allocator of dwellings:*";
P_HTM[8933]="*yo na chandāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na dosāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na mohāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na bhayāgatiṃ gaccheyya, gahitāgahitañca jāneyya.**he is not swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear, and he knows which dwellings have and have not been allocated.*";
P_HTM[8934]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sammannitabbo—**And he should be appointed like this.*";
P_HTM[8935]="*Paṭhamaṃ bhikkhu yācitabbo, yācitvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**First a monk should be asked, and then a competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[8936]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[8937]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ senāsanaggāhāpakaṃ sammanneyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should appoint monk so-and-so as allocator of dwellings.*";
P_HTM[8938]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[8939]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[8940]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ senāsanaggāhāpakaṃ sammannati.**The Sangha appoints monk so-and-so as allocator of dwellings.*";
P_HTM[8941]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno senāsanaggāhāpakassa sammuti, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of appointing monk so-and-so as allocator of dwellings should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[8942]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[8943]="*Sammato saṅghena itthannāmo bhikkhu senāsanaggāhāpako.**The Sangha has appointed monk so-and-so as allocator of dwellings.*";
P_HTM[8944]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[8945]="*Atha kho senāsanaggāhāpakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The allocators of dwellings thought,*";
P_HTM[8946]="*“kathaṃ nu kho senāsanaṃ gāhetabban”ti?**“How should we allocate the dwellings?”*";
P_HTM[8947]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[8948]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, paṭhamaṃ bhikkhū gaṇetuṃ, bhikkhū gaṇetvā seyyā gaṇetuṃ, seyyā gaṇetvā seyyaggena gāhetun”ti.**“First you should count the monks and the beds. You should then allocate one monk to each bed.”*";
P_HTM[8949]="*Seyyaggena gāhentā seyyā ussārayiṃsu …pe…**When they were allocating the beds, there were beds left over.*";
P_HTM[8950]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, vihāraggena gāhetun”ti.**“You should allocate one monk to each dwelling.”*";
P_HTM[8951]="*Vihāraggena gāhentā vihārā ussārayiṃsu …pe…**When they were allocating the dwellings, there were dwellings left over.*";
P_HTM[8952]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pariveṇaggena gāhetun”ti.**“You should allocate one monk to the precincts of each dwelling.”*";
P_HTM[8953]="*Pariveṇaggena gāhentā pariveṇā ussārayiṃsu …pe…**When they were allocating the precincts, there were precincts left over.*";
P_HTM[8954]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, anubhāgampi dātuṃ.**“You should give out additional shares.*";
P_HTM[8955]="*Gahite anubhāge añño bhikkhu āgacchati, akāmā na dātabbo”ti.**If another monk arrives after the additional shares have been allocated, then if you’re unwilling, you need not give him a share.”*";
P_HTM[8956]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū nissīme ṭhitassa senāsanaṃ gāhenti.**On one occasion the monks allocated a dwelling to one who was outside the monastic boundary.*";
P_HTM[8957]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8958]="*“Na, bhikkhave, nissīme ṭhitassa senāsanaṃ gāhetabbaṃ.**“You should not allocate a dwelling to one outside the monastic boundary.*";
P_HTM[8959]="*Yo gāheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[8960]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū senāsanaṃ gahetvā sabbakālaṃ paṭibāhanti.**At that time, after accepting a dwelling, the monks reserved it at all times.*";
P_HTM[8961]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8962]="*“Na, bhikkhave, senāsanaṃ gahetvā sabbakālaṃ paṭibāhitabbaṃ.**“After you have accepted a dwelling, you should not reserve it at all times.*";
P_HTM[8963]="*Yo paṭibāheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8964]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, vassānaṃ temāsaṃ paṭibāhituṃ, utukālaṃ pana na paṭibāhitun”ti.**I allow you to reserve it for the three months of the rainy-season residence, but not at other times.”*";
P_HTM[8965]="*Atha kho bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The monks thought,*";
P_HTM[8966]="*“kati nu kho senāsanaggāhā”ti?**“How many times are there for the allocation of dwellings?”*";
P_HTM[8967]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8968]="*“Tayo me, bhikkhave, senāsanaggāhā—**“There are three times for the allocation of dwellings:*";
P_HTM[8969]="*purimako, pacchimako, antarāmuttako.**the first, the second, and when given up in between.*";
P_HTM[8970]="*Aparajjugatāya āsāḷhiyā purimako gāhetabbo.**The first allocation is on the day after the full moon of July.*";
P_HTM[8971]="*Māsagatāya āsāḷhiyā pacchimako gāhetabbo.**The second allocation is one month after the full moon of July.*";
P_HTM[8972]="*Aparajjugatāya pavāraṇāya āyatiṃ vassāvāsatthāya antarāmuttako gāhetabbo.**The allocation of what is given up in between the two is on the day after the invitation procedure and is for the purpose of spending the next rains residence.”*";
P_HTM[8973]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo senāsanaggāhā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8974]="*Dutiyabhāṇavāro niṭṭhito.**The second section for recitation is finished.*";
P_HTM[8975]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto sāvatthiyaṃ senāsanaṃ gahetvā aññataraṃ gāmakāvāsaṃ agamāsi.**On one occasion Venerable Upananda the Sakyan had accepted a dwelling at Sāvatthī, but then went to a certain village monastery,*";
P_HTM[8976]="*Tatthapi senāsanaṃ aggahesi.**where he was also allocated a dwelling.*";
P_HTM[8977]="*Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The monks there thought,*";
P_HTM[8978]="*“ayaṃ, āvuso, āyasmā upanando sakyaputto bhaṇḍanakārako kalahakārako vivādakārako bhassakārako saṅghe adhikaraṇakārako.**“This Upananda is quarrelsome and argumentative, and creates legal issues in the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[8979]="*Sacāyaṃ idha vassaṃ vasissati, sabbeva mayaṃ na phāsu bhavissāma.**If he spends the rainy season here, none of us will be at ease.*";
P_HTM[8980]="*Handa naṃ pucchāmā”ti.**Well, let’s question him.”*";
P_HTM[8981]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ etadavocuṃ—**And they said to Upananda,*";
P_HTM[8982]="*“nanu tayā, āvuso upananda, sāvatthiyaṃ senāsanaṃ gahitan”ti?**“Have you not been allocated a dwelling at Sāvatthī? ”*";
P_HTM[8983]="*“Evamāvuso”ti.**“Yes, I have.”*";
P_HTM[8984]="*“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, āvuso upananda, eko dve paṭibāhasī”ti?**“But being only one person, why do you reserve two dwellings?”*";
P_HTM[8985]="*“Idha dānāhaṃ, āvuso, muñcāmi;**“I will give up this one*";
P_HTM[8986]="*tattha gaṇhāmī”ti.**and take the one at Sāvatthī.”*";
P_HTM[8987]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[8988]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto eko dve paṭibāhessatī”ti.**“How could Upananda reserve two dwellings for himself?”*";
P_HTM[8989]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned Upananda:*";
P_HTM[8990]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, eko dve paṭibāhasī”ti?**“Is it true, Upananda, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[8991]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[8992]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[8993]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, eko dve paṭibāhissasi?**“Foolish man, how can you reserve two dwellings for yourself?*";
P_HTM[8994]="*Tattha tayā, moghapurisa, gahitaṃ idha muttaṃ, idha tayā gahitaṃ tatra muttaṃ.**What you had been allocated at Sāvatthī, you gave up when you were allocated a dwelling here. And what you have been allocated here, you have now given up.*";
P_HTM[8995]="*Evaṃ kho tvaṃ, moghapurisa, ubhayattha paribāhiro.**You’re now excluded from both.*";
P_HTM[8996]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[8997]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after rebuking him …*";
P_HTM[8998]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[8999]="*“na, bhikkhave, ekena dve paṭibāhitabbā.**“A single monk should not reserve two dwellings.*";
P_HTM[9000]="*Yo paṭibāheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[9001]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā bhikkhūnaṃ anekapariyāyena vinayakathaṃ kathesi, vinayassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, vinayapariyattiyā vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, ādissa ādissa āyasmato upālissa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati.**At one time the Buddha gave many talks about the Monastic Law, spoke in praise of the Monastic Law and of learning the Monastic Law, and he repeatedly praised Venerable Upāli.*";
P_HTM[9002]="*Bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**When the monks*";
P_HTM[9003]="*“bhagavā kho anekapariyāyena vinayakathaṃ katheti, vinayassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, vinayapariyattiyā vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, ādissa ādissa āyasmato upālissa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati.**heard this, they thought,*";
P_HTM[9004]="*Handa mayaṃ, āvuso, āyasmato upālissa santike vinayaṃ pariyāpuṇāmā”ti.**“Well then, let’s learn the Monastic Law from Venerable Upāli.”*";
P_HTM[9005]="*Tedha bahū bhikkhū therā ca navā ca majjhimā ca āyasmato upālissa santike vinayaṃ pariyāpuṇanti.**And many monks, both senior and junior, as well as those of middle standing, learned the Monastic Law from Upāli.*";
P_HTM[9006]="*Āyasmā upāli ṭhitakova uddisati therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ gāravena.**Out of respect for the senior monks, Upāli taught while standing.*";
P_HTM[9007]="*Therāpi bhikkhū ṭhitakāva uddisāpenti dhammagāravena.**And out of respect for the Teaching, the senior monks, too, were standing.*";
P_HTM[9008]="*Tattha therā ceva bhikkhū kilamanti, āyasmā ca upāli kilamati.**Both the senior monks and Upāli became tired.*";
P_HTM[9009]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[9010]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, navakena bhikkhunā uddisantena samake vā āsane nisīdituṃ, uccatare vā dhammagāravena;**“A junior monk who is teaching should sit on a similar or higher seat out of respect for the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[9011]="*therena bhikkhunā uddisāpentena samake vā āsane nisīdituṃ, nīcatare vā dhammagāravenā”ti.**A senior monk who is being taught should sit on a similar or lower seat out of respect for the Teaching.”*";
P_HTM[9012]="*Tena kho pana samayena bahū bhikkhū āyasmato upālissa santike ṭhitakā uddesaṃ paṭimānentā kilamanti.**On one occasion many monks were standing in the presence of Upāli, honoring the recitation. They became tired.*";
P_HTM[9013]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9014]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, samānāsanikehi saha nisīditun”ti.**“I allow those who are entitled to a seat of the same height to sit together.”*";
P_HTM[9015]="*Atha kho bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The monks thought,*";
P_HTM[9016]="*“kittāvatā nu kho samānāsaniko hotī”ti?**“Who are entitled to a seat of the same height?”*";
P_HTM[9017]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ—* **";
P_HTM[9018]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tivassantarena saha nisīditun”ti.**“I allow those with a difference of three years or less in seniority to sit together.”*";
P_HTM[9019]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū samānāsanikā mañce nisīditvā mañcaṃ bhindiṃsu, pīṭhe nisīditvā pīṭhaṃ bhindiṃsu.**On one occasion a number of monks entitled to a seat of the same height were seated on a bed; the bed broke. They were seated on the same bench; the bench broke.*";
P_HTM[9020]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9021]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tivaggassa mañcaṃ, tivaggassa pīṭhan”ti.**“I allow a maximum of three on a bed or bench.”*";
P_HTM[9022]="*Tivaggopi mañce nisīditvā mañcaṃ bhindi, pīṭhe nisīditvā pīṭhaṃ bhindi …pe…**The beds and benches still broke.*";
P_HTM[9023]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, duvaggassa mañcaṃ, duvaggassa pīṭhan”ti.**“I allow a maximum of two on a bed or bench.”*";
P_HTM[9024]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū asamānāsanikehi saha dīghāsane nisīdituṃ kukkuccāyanti.**At that time, being afraid of wrongdoing, monks who were not entitled to a seat of the same height did not sit together on a long seat.*";
P_HTM[9025]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9026]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ṭhapetvā paṇḍakaṃ, mātugāmaṃ, ubhatobyañjanakaṃ, asamānāsanikehi saha dīghāsane nisīditun”ti.**“I allow those who are not entitled to a seat of the same height to sit together on a long seat, except with a _paṇḍaka_, a woman, or a hermaphrodite.”*";
P_HTM[9027]="*Atha kho bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The monks thought,*";
P_HTM[9028]="*“kittakaṃ pacchimaṃ nu kho dīghāsanaṃ hotī”ti?**“What is the size of the smallest long seat?”*";
P_HTM[9029]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9030]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, yaṃ tiṇṇaṃ pahoti, ettakaṃ pacchimaṃ dīghāsanan”ti.**“A seat for three is the smallest long seat.”*";
P_HTM[9031]="*Tena kho pana samayena visākhā migāramātā saṅghassa atthāya sāḷindaṃ pāsādaṃ kārāpetukāmā hoti hatthinakhakaṃ.**At one time Visākhā Migāramātā wanted to build a stilt house for the benefit of the Sangha, including a porch and elephant globes.*";
P_HTM[9032]="*Atha kho bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The monks thought,*";
P_HTM[9033]="*“kiṃ nu kho bhagavatā pāsādaparibhogo anuññāto kiṃ ananuññāto”ti?**“What stilt-house equipment has the Buddha allowed and what has he not allowed?”*";
P_HTM[9034]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[9035]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, sabbaṃ pāsādaparibhogan”ti.**“I allow all stilt-house equipment.”*";
P_HTM[9036]="*Tena kho pana samayena rañño pasenadissa kosalassa ayyikā kālaṅkatā hoti.**At one time King Pasenadi of Kosala’s grandmother had just died.*";
P_HTM[9037]="*Tassa kālaṅkiriyāya saṅghassa bahuṃ akappiyabhaṇḍaṃ uppannaṃ hoti, seyyathidaṃ—**As a result, many unallowable goods were given to the Sangha, that is:*";
P_HTM[9038]="*āsandi, pallaṅko, gonako, cittako, paṭikā, paṭalikā, tūlikā, vikatikā, uddalomī, ekantalomī, kaṭṭissaṃ, koseyyaṃ, kuttakaṃ, hatthattharaṃ, assattharaṃ, rathattharaṃ, ajinapaveṇi, kadalimigapavarapaccattharaṇaṃ, sauttaracchadaṃ, ubhatolohitakūpadhānaṃ.**a high couch, a luxurious couch, a long-fleeced woolen rug, a multi-colored woolen rug, a white woolen rug, a red woolen rug, a cotton-down quilt, a woolen rug decorated with the images of predatory animals, a woolen rug with long fleece on one side, a woolen rug with long fleece on both side, a sheet of silk embroidered with gems, a silken sheet, a woolen rug like a dancers’ rug, an elephant-back rug, a horse-back rug, a carriage-seat rug, a rug made of black antelope hide, an excellent rug made of _kadalī_-deer hide, a seat or bed with a canopy, a seat or bed with red cushions at each end.*";
P_HTM[9039]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9040]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, āsandiyā pāde chinditvā paribhuñjituṃ, pallaṅkassa vāḷe bhinditvā paribhuñjituṃ, tūlikaṃ vijaṭetvā bibbohanaṃ kātuṃ, avasesaṃ bhūmattharaṇaṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to use a high couch after cutting its legs down to size, to use a luxurious couch after removing the images of predatory animals, to make a pillow after removing the cotton down from the cotton-down quilt, and to make floor covers of the rest.”*";
P_HTM[9041]="*1. Avissajjiyavatthu**3.1 What is not to be given away*";
P_HTM[9042]="*Tena kho pana samayena sāvatthiyā avidūre aññatarasmiṃ gāmakāvāse āvāsikā bhikkhū upaddutā honti āgantukagamikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ senāsanaṃ paññapentā.**At one time in a village monastery not far from Sāvatthī the resident monks were fed up with assigning dwellings for newly arrived and departing monks.*";
P_HTM[9043]="*Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**They considered this*";
P_HTM[9044]="*“etarahi kho mayaṃ, āvuso, upaddutā āgantukagamikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ senāsanaṃ paññapentā.* **";
P_HTM[9045]="*Handa mayaṃ, āvuso, sabbaṃ saṅghikaṃ senāsanaṃ ekassa dema.**and thought, “Well, let’s give all the dwellings belonging to the Sangha to one of us.*";
P_HTM[9046]="*Tassa santakaṃ paribhuñjissāmā”ti.**We’ll then use what belongs to him.”*";
P_HTM[9047]="*Te sabbaṃ saṅghikaṃ senāsanaṃ ekassa adaṃsu.**And they did just that.*";
P_HTM[9048]="*Āgantukā bhikkhū te bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—**When newly arrived monks said to them,*";
P_HTM[9049]="*“amhākaṃ, āvuso, senāsanaṃ paññapethā”ti.**“Please assign us a dwelling,”*";
P_HTM[9050]="*“Natthāvuso, saṅghikaṃ senāsanaṃ;**they replied, “There are no dwellings belonging to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[9051]="*sabbaṃ amhehi ekassa dinnan”ti.**They have all been given to one of us.”*";
P_HTM[9052]="*“Kiṃ pana tumhe, āvuso, saṅghikaṃ senāsanaṃ vissajjethā”ti?**“So you have given away the dwellings belonging to the Sangha?”*";
P_HTM[9053]="*“Evamāvuso”ti.**“Yes.”*";
P_HTM[9054]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[9055]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū saṅghikaṃ senāsanaṃ vissajjessantī”ti.**“How can monks give away dwellings belonging to the Sangha?”*";
P_HTM[9056]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[9057]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū saṅghikaṃ senāsanaṃ vissajjentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that they did this?”*";
P_HTM[9058]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[9059]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them,*";
P_HTM[9060]="*kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā saṅghikaṃ senāsanaṃ vissajjessanti?**“How can those foolish men give away dwellings belonging to the Sangha?*";
P_HTM[9061]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[9062]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[9063]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[9064]="*“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, avissajjiyāni, na vissajjetabbāni, saṅghena vā gaṇena vā puggalena vā.**“There are five things not to be given away, either by a sangha, a group, or an individual.*";
P_HTM[9065]="*Vissajjitānipi avissajjitāni honti.**Even if given away, they are not actually given away.*";
P_HTM[9066]="*Yo vissajjeyya, āpatti thullaccayassa.**If you give any of them away, you commit a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[9067]="*Katamāni pañca?**What are the five?*";
P_HTM[9068]="*Ārāmo, ārāmavatthu—**A monastery or the site of a monastery;*";
P_HTM[9069]="*idaṃ paṭhamaṃ avissajjiyaṃ, na vissajjetabbaṃ, saṅghena vā gaṇena vā puggalena vā.* **";
P_HTM[9070]="*Vissajjitampi avissajjitaṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[9071]="*Yo vissajjeyya, āpatti thullaccayassa.* **";
P_HTM[9072]="*Vihāro, vihāravatthu—**A dwelling or the site of a dwelling;*";
P_HTM[9073]="*idaṃ dutiyaṃ avissajjiyaṃ, na vissajjetabbaṃ, saṅghena vā gaṇena vā puggalena vā.* **";
P_HTM[9074]="*Vissajjitampi avissajjitaṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[9075]="*Yo vissajjeyya, āpatti thullaccayassa.* **";
P_HTM[9076]="*Mañco, pīṭhaṃ, bhisi, bibbohanaṃ—**A bed, bench, mattress, or pillow;*";
P_HTM[9077]="*idaṃ tatiyaṃ avissajjiyaṃ, na vissajjetabbaṃ, saṅghena vā gaṇena vā puggalena vā.* **";
P_HTM[9078]="*Vissajjitampi avissajjitaṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[9079]="*Yo vissajjeyya, āpatti thullaccayassa.* **";
P_HTM[9080]="*Lohakumbhī, lohabhāṇakaṃ, lohavārako, lohakaṭāhaṃ, vāsi, parasu, kuṭhārī, kudālo, nikhādanaṃ—**A metal pot, a metal jar, a metal bucket, a metal bowl, a adz, a hatchet, an ax, a spade, or a chisel;*";
P_HTM[9081]="*idaṃ catutthaṃ avissajjiyaṃ, na vissajjetabbaṃ, saṅghena vā gaṇena vā puggalena vā.* **";
P_HTM[9082]="*Vissajjitampi avissajjitaṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[9083]="*Yo vissajjeyya, āpatti thullaccayassa.* **";
P_HTM[9084]="*Valli, veḷu, muñjaṃ, pabbajaṃ, tiṇaṃ, mattikā, dārubhaṇḍaṃ, mattikābhaṇḍaṃ—**A creeper, bamboo, reed, grass, clay, wooden goods, or ceramic goods.*";
P_HTM[9085]="*idaṃ pañcamaṃ avissajjiyaṃ, na vissajjetabbaṃ, saṅghena vā gaṇena vā puggalena vā.* **";
P_HTM[9086]="*Vissajjitampi avissajjitaṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[9087]="*Yo vissajjeyya, āpatti thullaccayassa.* **";
P_HTM[9088]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca avissajjiyāni, na vissajjetabbāni, saṅghena vā gaṇena vā puggalena vā.**These are the five things not to be given away, either by a sangha, a group, or an individual.*";
P_HTM[9089]="*Vissajjitānipi avissajjitāni honti.**Even if given away, they are not actually given away.*";
P_HTM[9090]="*Yo vissajjeyya, āpatti thullaccayassā”ti.**If you give any of them away, you commit a serious offense.”*";
P_HTM[9091]="*2. Avebhaṅgiyavatthu**3.2 What is not to be shared out*";
P_HTM[9092]="*Atha kho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena kīṭāgiri tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi sāriputtamoggallānehi ca.**When the Buddha had stayed at Sāvatthī for as long as he liked, he set out wandering toward Kīṭāgiri with a large sangha of five hundred monks, including Sāriputta and Mahāmoggallāna.*";
P_HTM[9093]="*Assosuṃ kho assajipunabbasukā bhikkhū—**The monks Assaji and Punabbasuka heard about this and said,*";
P_HTM[9094]="*“bhagavā kira kīṭāgiriṃ āgacchati mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi sāriputtamoggallānehi ca.* **";
P_HTM[9095]="*Handa mayaṃ, āvuso, sabbaṃ saṅghikaṃ senāsanaṃ bhājema.**“Well, let’s share out all the dwellings belonging to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[9096]="*Pāpicchā sāriputtamoggallānā, pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gatā;**Sāriputta and Mahāmoggallāna are in the grip of bad desires.*";
P_HTM[9097]="*na mayaṃ tesaṃ senāsanaṃ paññapessāmā”ti, te sabbaṃ saṅghikaṃ senāsanaṃ bhājesuṃ.**We won’t assign dwellings to them.” And they shared out all the dwellings belonging to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[9098]="*Atha kho bhagavā anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena kīṭāgiri tadavasari.**The Buddha eventually arrived at Kīṭāgiri.*";
P_HTM[9099]="*Atha kho bhagavā sambahule bhikkhū āmantesi—**And he said to a group of monks,*";
P_HTM[9100]="*“gacchatha tumhe, bhikkhave;* **";
P_HTM[9101]="*assajipunabbasuke bhikkhū upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadetha—**“Go to the monks Assaji and Punabbasuka and say,*";
P_HTM[9102]="*‘bhagavā, āvuso, āgacchati mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi sāriputtamoggallānehi ca.**‘The Buddha is coming with a large sangha of five hundred monks, including Sāriputta and Mahāmoggallāna.*";
P_HTM[9103]="*Bhagavato ca, āvuso, senāsanaṃ paññapetha, bhikkhusaṅghassa ca, sāriputtamoggallānānañcā’”ti.**Assign dwellings to the Buddha, to the Sangha of monks, and to Sāriputta and Mahāmoggallāna.’”*";
P_HTM[9104]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paṭissutvā yena assajipunabbasukā bhikkhū tenupasaṅkamiṃsu, upasaṅkamitvā assajipunabbasuke bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—**Saying, “Yes, Sir,” they did just that.*";
P_HTM[9105]="*“bhagavā, āvuso, āgacchati mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi sāriputtamoggallānehi ca.* **";
P_HTM[9106]="*Bhagavato ca, āvuso, senāsanaṃ paññapetha, bhikkhusaṅghassa ca, sāriputtamoggallānānañcā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[9107]="*“Natthāvuso, saṅghikaṃ senāsanaṃ.**The monks Assaji and Punabbasuka replied, “There are no dwellings belonging to the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[9108]="*Sabbaṃ amhehi bhājitaṃ.**they have all been shared out by us.*";
P_HTM[9109]="*Svāgataṃ, āvuso, bhagavato.**The Buddha is welcome*";
P_HTM[9110]="*Yasmiṃ vihāre bhagavā icchissati tasmiṃ vihāre vasissati.**and he may stay wherever he likes.*";
P_HTM[9111]="*Pāpicchā sāriputtamoggallānā, pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gatā.**But Sāriputta and Mahāmoggallāna are in the grip of bad desires.*";
P_HTM[9112]="*Na mayaṃ tesaṃ senāsanaṃ paññapessāmā”ti.**We won’t assign dwellings to them.”*";
P_HTM[9113]="*“Kiṃ pana tumhe, āvuso, saṅghikaṃ senāsanaṃ bhājitthā”ti?**“So you have shared out the dwellings belonging to the Sangha?”*";
P_HTM[9114]="*“Evamāvuso”ti.**“Yes.”*";
P_HTM[9115]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[9116]="*“kathañhi nāma assajipunabbasukā bhikkhū saṅghikaṃ senāsanaṃ bhājessantī”ti.**“How can these monks share out dwellings belonging to the Sangha?”*";
P_HTM[9117]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[9118]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave …pe…**“Is it true, monks, that they did this?”*";
P_HTM[9119]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[9120]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them,*";
P_HTM[9121]="*kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā saṅghikaṃ senāsanaṃ bhājessanti?**“How can those foolish men share out the dwellings belonging to the Sangha?*";
P_HTM[9122]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[9123]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[9124]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[9125]="*“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, avebhaṅgiyāni, na vibhajitabbāni, saṅghena vā gaṇena vā puggalena vā.**“There are five things not to be shared out, either by a sangha, a group, or an individual.*";
P_HTM[9126]="*Vibhattānipi avibhattāni honti.**Even if shared out, they are not actually shared out.*";
P_HTM[9127]="*Yo vibhajeyya, āpatti thullaccayassa.**If you share out any of them, you commit a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[9128]="*Katamāni pañca?**What are the five?*";
P_HTM[9129]="*Ārāmo, ārāmavatthu—**A monastery or the land of a monastery;*";
P_HTM[9130]="*idaṃ paṭhamaṃ avebhaṅgiyaṃ, na vibhajitabbaṃ, saṅghena vā gaṇena vā puggalena vā.* **";
P_HTM[9131]="*Vibhattampi avibhattaṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[9132]="*Yo vibhajeyya, āpatti thullaccayassa.* **";
P_HTM[9133]="*Vihāro, vihāravatthu—**A dwelling or the land of a dwelling;*";
P_HTM[9134]="*idaṃ dutiyaṃ avebhaṅgiyaṃ, na vibhajitabbaṃ, saṅghena vā gaṇena vā puggalena vā.* **";
P_HTM[9135]="*Vibhattampi avibhattaṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[9136]="*Yo vibhajeyya, āpatti thullaccayassa.* **";
P_HTM[9137]="*Mañco, pīṭhaṃ, bhisi, bibbohanaṃ—**A bed, bench, mattress, or pillow;*";
P_HTM[9138]="*idaṃ tatiyaṃ avebhaṅgiyaṃ, na vibhajitabbaṃ, saṅghena vā gaṇena vā puggalena vā.* **";
P_HTM[9139]="*Vibhattampi avibhattaṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[9140]="*Yo vibhajeyya, āpatti thullaccayassa.* **";
P_HTM[9141]="*Lohakumbhī, lohabhāṇakaṃ, lohavārako, lohakaṭāhaṃ, vāsī, parasu, kuṭhārī, kudālo, nikhādanaṃ—**A metal pot, a metal jar, a metal bucket, a metal bowl, a adz, a hatchet, an ax, a spade, or a chisel;*";
P_HTM[9142]="*idaṃ catutthaṃ avebhaṅgiyaṃ, na vibhajitabbaṃ, saṅghena vā gaṇena vā puggalena vā.* **";
P_HTM[9143]="*Vibhattampi avibhattaṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[9144]="*Yo vibhajeyya, āpatti thullaccayassa.* **";
P_HTM[9145]="*Vallī, veḷu, muñjaṃ, pabbajaṃ, tiṇaṃ, mattikā, dārubhaṇḍaṃ, mattikābhaṇḍaṃ—**A creeper, bamboo, reed, grass, clay, wooden goods, or ceramic goods.*";
P_HTM[9146]="*idaṃ pañcamaṃ avebhaṅgiyaṃ, na vibhajitabbaṃ, saṅghena vā gaṇena vā puggalena vā.* **";
P_HTM[9147]="*Vibhattampi avibhattaṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[9148]="*Yo vibhajeyya, āpatti thullaccayassa.* **";
P_HTM[9149]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca avebhaṅgiyāni, na vibhajitabbāni, saṅghena vā gaṇena vā puggalena vā.**These are the five things not to be shared out, either by a sangha, a group, or an individual.*";
P_HTM[9150]="*Vibhattānipi avibhattāni honti.**Even if shared out, they are not actually shared out.*";
P_HTM[9151]="*Yo vibhajeyya, āpatti thullaccayassā”ti.**If you share out any of them, you commit a serious offense.”*";
P_HTM[9152]="*3. Navakammadānakathā**3.3 Discussion on putting in charge of building work*";
P_HTM[9153]="*Atha kho bhagavā kīṭāgirismiṃ yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena āḷavī tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**When the Buddha had stayed at Kīṭāgiri for as long as he liked, he set out wandering toward Āḷavī.*";
P_HTM[9154]="*Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena āḷavī tadavasari.**When he eventually arrived,*";
P_HTM[9155]="*Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā āḷaviyaṃ viharati aggāḷave cetiye.**he stayed at Aggāḷava Shrine.*";
P_HTM[9156]="*Tena kho pana samayena āḷavakā bhikkhū evarūpāni navakammāni denti—**At that time the monks of Āḷava put monks in charge of building work such as this:*";
P_HTM[9157]="*piṇḍanikkhepanamattenapi navakammaṃ denti;**the mere filling of gaps,*";
P_HTM[9158]="*kuṭṭalepanamattenapi navakammaṃ denti;**the mere plastering of walls,*";
P_HTM[9159]="*dvāraṭṭhapanamattenapi navakammaṃ denti;**the mere hanging of doors,*";
P_HTM[9160]="*aggaḷavaṭṭikaraṇamattenapi navakammaṃ denti;**the mere making of bolt-receiving posts,*";
P_HTM[9161]="*ālokasandhikaraṇamattenapi navakammaṃ denti;**the mere making of windows,*";
P_HTM[9162]="*setavaṇṇakaraṇamattenapi navakammaṃ denti;**the mere application of white coloring,*";
P_HTM[9163]="*kāḷavaṇṇakaraṇamattenapi navakammaṃ denti;**the mere application of black coloring,*";
P_HTM[9164]="*gerukaparikammakaraṇamattenapi navakammaṃ denti;**the mere treatment with red ocher,*";
P_HTM[9165]="*chādanamattenapi navakammaṃ denti;**the mere covering with a roof,*";
P_HTM[9166]="*bandhanamattenapi navakammaṃ denti;**the mere fastening of a roof,*";
P_HTM[9167]="*bhaṇḍikāṭṭhapanamattenapi navakammaṃ denti;**the mere fixing of cornices,*";
P_HTM[9168]="*khaṇḍaphullapaṭisaṅkharaṇamattenapi navakammaṃ denti;**the mere repair of what is defective or broken,*";
P_HTM[9169]="*paribhaṇḍakaraṇamattenapi navakammaṃ denti;**the mere plastering of a floor;*";
P_HTM[9170]="*vīsativassikampi navakammaṃ denti;**and they put monks in charge of building work for twenty years,*";
P_HTM[9171]="*tiṃsavassikampi navakammaṃ denti;**for thirty years,*";
P_HTM[9172]="*yāvajīvikampi navakammaṃ denti;**for life;*";
P_HTM[9173]="*dhūmakālikampi pariyositaṃ vihāraṃ navakammaṃ denti.**and they put monks in charge of building work for life on finished dwellings.*";
P_HTM[9174]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[9175]="*“kathañhi nāma āḷavakā bhikkhū evarūpāni navakammāni dassanti—**“How can the monks at Āḷavī put monks in charge of such kinds of work?”*";
P_HTM[9176]="*piṇḍanikkhepanamattenapi navakammaṃ dassanti;* **";
P_HTM[9177]="*kuṭṭalepanamattenapi …* **";
P_HTM[9178]="*dvāraṭṭhapanamattenapi …* **";
P_HTM[9179]="*aggaḷavaṭṭikaraṇamattenapi …* **";
P_HTM[9180]="*ālokasandhikaraṇamattenapi …* **";
P_HTM[9181]="*setavaṇṇakaraṇamattenapi …* **";
P_HTM[9182]="*kāḷavaṇṇakaraṇamattenapi …* **";
P_HTM[9183]="*gerukaparikammakaraṇamattenapi …* **";
P_HTM[9184]="*chādanamattenapi …* **";
P_HTM[9185]="*bandhanamattenapi …* **";
P_HTM[9186]="*bhaṇḍikāṭṭhapanamattenapi …* **";
P_HTM[9187]="*khaṇḍaphullapaṭisaṅkharaṇamattenapi …* **";
P_HTM[9188]="*paribhaṇḍakaraṇamattenapi …* **";
P_HTM[9189]="*vīsativassikampi …* **";
P_HTM[9190]="*tiṃsavassikampi …* **";
P_HTM[9191]="*yāvajīvikampi …* **";
P_HTM[9192]="*dhūmakālikampi pariyositaṃ vihāraṃ navakammaṃ dassantī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[9193]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. …*";
P_HTM[9194]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave …pe…**“Is it true, monks, that they do this?”*";
P_HTM[9195]="*“saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[9196]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[9197]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[9198]="*“na, bhikkhave, piṇḍanikkhepanamattena navakammaṃ dātabbaṃ …pe…**“You should not put monks in charge of building work such as this: the mere filling of gaps,*";
P_HTM[9199]="*na kuṭṭalepanamattena navakammaṃ dātabbaṃ.**the mere plastering of walls,*";
P_HTM[9200]="*Na dvāraṭṭhapanamattena navakammaṃ dātabbaṃ.**the mere hanging of doors,*";
P_HTM[9201]="*Na aggaḷavaṭṭikaraṇamattena navakammaṃ dātabbaṃ.**the mere making of bolt-receiving posts,*";
P_HTM[9202]="*Na ālokasandhikaraṇamattena navakammaṃ dātabbaṃ.**the mere making of windows,*";
P_HTM[9203]="*Na setavaṇṇakaraṇamattena navakammaṃ dātabbaṃ.**the mere application of white coloring,*";
P_HTM[9204]="*Na kāḷavaṇṇakaraṇamattena navakammaṃ dātabbaṃ.**the mere application of black coloring,*";
P_HTM[9205]="*Na gerukaparikammakaraṇamattena navakammaṃ dātabbaṃ.**the mere treatment with red ocher,*";
P_HTM[9206]="*Na chādanamattena navakammaṃ dātabbaṃ.**the mere covering with a roof,*";
P_HTM[9207]="*Na bandhanamattena navakammaṃ dātabbaṃ.**the mere fastening of a roof,*";
P_HTM[9208]="*Na bhaṇḍikāṭṭhapanamattena navakammaṃ dātabbaṃ.**the mere fixing of cornices,*";
P_HTM[9209]="*Na khaṇḍaphullapaṭisaṅkharaṇamattena navakammaṃ dātabbaṃ.**the mere repair of what is defective or broken,*";
P_HTM[9210]="*Na paribhaṇḍakaraṇamattena navakammaṃ dātabbaṃ.**or the mere plastering of a floor;*";
P_HTM[9211]="*Na vīsativassikaṃ navakammaṃ dātabbaṃ.**and you should not put monks in charge of building work for twenty years,*";
P_HTM[9212]="*Na tiṃsavassikaṃ navakammaṃ dātabbaṃ.**for thirty years,*";
P_HTM[9213]="*Na yāvajīvikaṃ navakammaṃ dātabbaṃ.**for life,*";
P_HTM[9214]="*Na dhūmakālikampi pariyositaṃ vihāraṃ navakammaṃ dātabbaṃ.**or put monks in charge of building work for life on finished dwellings.*";
P_HTM[9215]="*Yo dadeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9216]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, akataṃ vā vippakataṃ vā navakammaṃ dātuṃ, khuddake vihāre kammaṃ oloketvā chappañcavassikaṃ navakammaṃ dātuṃ, aḍḍhayoge kammaṃ oloketvā sattaṭṭhavassikaṃ navakammaṃ dātuṃ, mahallake vihāre pāsāde vā kammaṃ oloketvā dasadvādasavassikaṃ navakammaṃ dātun”ti.**I allow you to put a monk in charge of building work that isn’t yet started or that’s partially complete. For a small dwelling, after inspecting the work, you may put a monk in charge of the building work for five or six years. For a small stilt house, after inspecting the work, you may put a monk in charge of the building work for seven or eight years. For a large dwelling or stilt house, after inspecting the work, you may put a monk in charge of the building work for ten or twelve years.”*";
P_HTM[9217]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū sabbe vihāre navakammaṃ denti.**On one occasion the monks put one person in charge of building work on all the dwellings.*";
P_HTM[9218]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9219]="*“Na, bhikkhave, sabbe vihāre navakammaṃ dātabbaṃ.**“You should not put one person in charge of building work on all the dwellings.*";
P_HTM[9220]="*Yo dadeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[9221]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū ekassa dve denti.**On one occasion the monks put one person in charge of building work on two dwellings.*";
P_HTM[9222]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9223]="*“Na, bhikkhave, ekassa dve dātabbā.**“You should not put one person in charge of building work on two dwellings.*";
P_HTM[9224]="*Yo dadeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[9225]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū navakammaṃ gahetvā aññaṃ vāsenti.**On one occasion the monks who had taken on building work had someone else stay in the dwelling.*";
P_HTM[9226]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9227]="*“Na, bhikkhave, navakammaṃ gahetvā añño vāsetabbo.**“When you have taken on building work, you should not have someone else stay in that dwelling.*";
P_HTM[9228]="*Yo vāseyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[9229]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū navakammaṃ gahetvā saṅghikaṃ paṭibāhenti.**At one time monks who had taken on building work reserved what belonged to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[9230]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9231]="*“Na, bhikkhave, navakammaṃ gahetvā saṅghikaṃ paṭibāhitabbaṃ.**“When you have taken on building work, you should not reserve what belongs to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[9232]="*Yo paṭibāheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9233]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ekaṃ varaseyyaṃ gahetun”ti.**I allow you to take one good bed.”*";
P_HTM[9234]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū nissīme ṭhitassa navakammaṃ denti.**On one occasion the monks put one who was outside the monastic boundary in charge of building work.*";
P_HTM[9235]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9236]="*“Na, bhikkhave, nissīme ṭhitassa navakammaṃ dātabbaṃ.**“You should not put one who is outside the monastic boundary in charge of building work.*";
P_HTM[9237]="*Yo dadeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[9238]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū navakammaṃ gahetvā sabbakālaṃ paṭibāhanti.**At one time the monks who had taken on building work reserved a dwelling at all times.*";
P_HTM[9239]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9240]="*“Na, bhikkhave, navakammaṃ gahetvā sabbakālaṃ paṭibāhitabbaṃ.**“When you have taken on building work, you should not reserve a dwelling at all times.*";
P_HTM[9241]="*Yo paṭibāheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9242]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, vassānaṃ temāsaṃ paṭibāhituṃ, utukālaṃ pana na paṭibāhitun”ti.**I allow you to reserve it for the three months of the rainy-season residence, but not at other times.”*";
P_HTM[9243]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū navakammaṃ gahetvā pakkamantipi, vibbhamantipi, kālampi karonti;**At that time monks who had taken on building work left, disrobed, died,*";
P_HTM[9244]="*sāmaṇerāpi paṭijānanti;**admitted to being novice monks,*";
P_HTM[9245]="*sikkhaṃ paccakkhātakāpi paṭijānanti;**admitted to having renounced the training,*";
P_HTM[9246]="*antimavatthuṃ ajjhāpannakāpi paṭijānanti;**admitted to having committed the worst kind of offense,*";
P_HTM[9247]="*ummattakāpi paṭijānanti;**admitted to being insane,*";
P_HTM[9248]="*khittacittāpi paṭijānanti;**admitted to being deranged,*";
P_HTM[9249]="*vedanāṭṭāpi paṭijānanti;**admitted to being overwhelmed by pain,*";
P_HTM[9250]="*āpattiyā adassane ukkhittakāpi paṭijānanti;**admitted to having been suspended for not recognizing an offense,*";
P_HTM[9251]="*āpattiyā appaṭikamme ukkhittakāpi paṭijānanti;**admitted to having been suspended for not making amends for an offense,*";
P_HTM[9252]="*pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge ukkhittakāpi paṭijānanti;**admitted to having been suspended for not giving up a bad view,*";
P_HTM[9253]="*paṇḍakāpi paṭijānanti;**admitted to being a _paṇḍaka_,*";
P_HTM[9254]="*theyyasaṃvāsakāpi paṭijānanti;**admitted to be living in the community by theft,*";
P_HTM[9255]="*titthiyapakkantakāpi paṭijānanti;**admitted to previously having left to join the monastics of another religion,*";
P_HTM[9256]="*tiracchānagatāpi paṭijānanti;**admitted to being an animal,*";
P_HTM[9257]="*mātughātakāpi paṭijānanti;**admitted to being a matricide,*";
P_HTM[9258]="*pitughātakāpi paṭijānanti;**admitted to being a patricide,*";
P_HTM[9259]="*arahantaghātakāpi paṭijānanti;**admitted to being a murderer of a perfected one,*";
P_HTM[9260]="*bhikkhunidūsakāpi paṭijānanti;**admitted to having raped a nun,*";
P_HTM[9261]="*saṅghabhedakāpi paṭijānanti;**admitted to having caused a schism in the Sangha,*";
P_HTM[9262]="*lohituppādakāpi paṭijānanti;**admitted to having caused the Buddha to bleed,*";
P_HTM[9263]="*ubhatobyañjanakāpi paṭijānanti.**admitted to being a hermaphrodite.*";
P_HTM[9264]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[9265]="*“Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu navakammaṃ gahetvā pakkamati—**“If a monk who has taken on building work departs,*";
P_HTM[9266]="*mā saṅghassa hāyīti aññassa dātabbaṃ.**it should be given to another, with the thought, ‘What belongs to the Sangha should not be allowed to deteriorate.’*";
P_HTM[9267]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu navakammaṃ gahetvā vibbhamati …pe…**If a monk who has taken on building work disrobes,*";
P_HTM[9268]="*kālaṃ karoti, sāmaṇero paṭijānāti, sikkhaṃ paccakkhātako paṭijānāti, antimavatthuṃ ajjhāpannako paṭijānāti, ummattako paṭijānāti, khittacitto paṭijānāti, vedanāṭṭo paṭijānāti, āpattiyā adassane ukkhittako paṭijānāti, āpattiyā appaṭikamme ukkhittako paṭijānāti, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge ukkhittako paṭijānāti, paṇḍako paṭijānāti, theyyasaṃvāsako paṭijānāti, titthiyapakkantako paṭijānāti, tiracchānagato paṭijānāti, mātughātako paṭijānāti, pitughātako paṭijānāti, arahantaghātako paṭijānāti, bhikkhunidūsako paṭijānāti, saṅghabhedako paṭijānāti, lohituppādako paṭijānāti, ubhatobyañjanako paṭijānāti—**dies, admits to being a novice monk, admits to having renounced the training, admits to having committed the worst kind of offense, admits to being insane, admits to being deranged, admits to being overwhelmed by pain, admits to having been suspended for not recognizing an offense, admits to having been suspended for not making amends for an offense, admits to having been suspended for not giving up a bad view, admits to being a _paṇḍaka_, admits to be living in the community by theft, admits to previously having left to join the monastics of another religion, admits to being an animal, admits to being a matricide, admits to being a patricide, admits to being a murderer of a perfected one, admits to having raped a nun, admits to having caused a schism in the Sangha, admits to having caused the Buddha to bleed, or admits to being a hermaphrodite,*";
P_HTM[9269]="*mā saṅghassa hāyīti aññassa dātabbaṃ.**it should be given to another, with the thought, ‘What belongs to the Sangha should not be allowed to deteriorate.’*";
P_HTM[9270]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu navakammaṃ gahetvā vippakate pakkamati—**If a monk who has taken on building work departs while it is still unfinished,*";
P_HTM[9271]="*mā saṅghassa hāyīti aññassa dātabbaṃ.**it should be given to another, with the thought, ‘What belongs to the Sangha should not be allowed to deteriorate.’*";
P_HTM[9272]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu navakammaṃ gahetvā vippakate vibbhamati …pe…**If a monk who has taken on building work disrobes while it is still unfinished …*";
P_HTM[9273]="*ubhatobyañjanako paṭijānāti—**admits to being a hermaphrodite while it is still unfinished,*";
P_HTM[9274]="*mā saṅghassa hāyīti aññassa dātabbaṃ.**it should be given to another, with the thought, ‘What belongs to the Sangha should not be allowed to deteriorate.’*";
P_HTM[9275]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu navakammaṃ gahetvā pariyosite pakkamati—**If a monk who has taken on building work departs when it is finished,*";
P_HTM[9276]="*tassevetaṃ.**then it is still for him.*";
P_HTM[9277]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu navakammaṃ gahetvā pariyosite vibbhamati …pe…**If a monk who has taken on building work disrobes when it is finished;*";
P_HTM[9278]="*kālaṃ karoti, sāmaṇero paṭijānāti, sikkhaṃ paccakkhātako paṭijānāti, antimavatthuṃ ajjhāpannako paṭijānāti—**dies when it is finished; admits, when it is finished, to being a novice monk; admits, when it is finished, to having renounced the training; or admits, when it is finished, to having committed the worst kind of offense,*";
P_HTM[9279]="*saṅgho sāmī.**then the Sangha is the owner.*";
P_HTM[9280]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu navakammaṃ gahetvā pariyosite ummattako paṭijānāti, khittacitto paṭijānāti, vedanāṭṭo paṭijānāti, āpattiyā adassane ukkhittako paṭijānāti, āpattiyā appaṭikamme ukkhittako paṭijānāti, pāpikāya diṭṭhiyā appaṭinissagge ukkhittako paṭijānāti—**If a monk who has taken on building work admits, when it is finished, to being insane; admits, when it is finished, to being deranged; admits, when it is finished, to being overwhelmed by pain; admits, when it is finished, to having been suspended for not recognizing an offense; admits, when it is finished, to having been suspended for not making amends for an offense; or admits, when it is finished, to having been suspended for not giving up a bad view,*";
P_HTM[9281]="*tassevetaṃ.**then it is still for him.*";
P_HTM[9282]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu navakammaṃ gahetvā pariyosite paṇḍako paṭijānāti, theyyasaṃvāsako paṭijānāti, titthiyapakkantako paṭijānāti, tiracchānagato paṭijānāti, mātughātako paṭijānāti, pitughātako paṭijānāti, arahantaghātako paṭijānāti, bhikkhunidūsako paṭijānāti, saṅghabhedako paṭijānāti, lohituppādako paṭijānāti, ubhatobyañjanako paṭijānāti—**If a monk who has taken on building work admits, when it is finished, to being a _paṇḍaka_; admits, when it is finished, to be living in the community by theft; admits, when it is finished, to previously having left to join the monastics of another religion; admits, when it is finished, to being an animal; admits, when it is finished, to being a matricide; admits, when it is finished, to being a patricide; admits, when it is finished, to being a murderer of a perfected one; admits, when it is finished, to having raped a nun; admits, when it is finished, to having caused a schism in the Sangha; admits, when it is finished, to having caused the Buddha to bleed; or admits, when it is finished, to being a hermaphrodite,*";
P_HTM[9283]="*saṅgho sāmī”ti.**then the Sangha is the owner.”*";
P_HTM[9284]="*4. Aññatraparibhogapaṭikkhepādi**3.4 The prohibition against using requisites where they don’t belong, etc.*";
P_HTM[9285]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū aññatarassa upāsakassa vihāraparibhogaṃ senāsanaṃ aññatra paribhuñjanti.**At one time the monks used a certain lay follower’s furniture where it did not belong.*";
P_HTM[9286]="*Atha kho so upāsako ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**That lay follower complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[9287]="*“kathañhi nāma bhadantā aññatra paribhogaṃ aññatra paribhuñjissantī”ti.**“How can those venerables use the furniture where it doesn’t belong?”*";
P_HTM[9288]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[9289]="*“Na, bhikkhave, aññatra paribhogo aññatra paribhuñjitabbo.**“You should not use furniture where it doesn’t belong.*";
P_HTM[9290]="*Yo paribhuñjeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[9291]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū uposathaggampi sannisajjampi harituṃ kukkuccāyantā chamāya nisīdanti.**Being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not take any equipment to the observance-day hall or to meetings, and they sat down on the bare ground.*";
P_HTM[9292]="*Gattānipi cīvarānipi paṃsukitāni honti.**Their limbs and robes became dirty.*";
P_HTM[9293]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9294]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tāvakālikaṃ haritun”ti.**“I allow you to borrow.”*";
P_HTM[9295]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa mahāvihāro undriyati.**At that time a large dwelling belonging to the Sangha was decaying.*";
P_HTM[9296]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā senāsanaṃ nātiharanti.**Being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not remove the furniture.*";
P_HTM[9297]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9298]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, guttatthāya haritun”ti.**“I allow you to move it for the purpose of protection.”*";
P_HTM[9299]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa senāsanaparikkhāriko mahaggho kambalo uppanno hoti.**On one occasion the Sangha was given a valuable, woolen furniture cloth.*";
P_HTM[9300]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9301]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, phātikammatthāya parivattetun”ti.**“I allow you to make a beneficial swap.”*";
P_HTM[9302]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa senāsanaparikkhārikaṃ mahagghaṃ dussaṃ uppannaṃ hoti.**On one occasion the Sangha was given a valuable furniture cloth.*";
P_HTM[9303]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9304]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, phātikammatthāya parivattetun”ti.**“I allow you to make a beneficial swap.”*";
P_HTM[9305]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa acchacammaṃ uppannaṃ hoti.**On one occasion the Sangha was given a bear skin.*";
P_HTM[9306]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9307]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pādapuñchaniṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to make it into a doormat.”*";
P_HTM[9308]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa cakkalikaṃ uppannaṃ hoti.**On one occasion the Sangha was given a round pad.*";
P_HTM[9309]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9310]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pādapuñchaniṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to make it into a doormat.”*";
P_HTM[9311]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa coḷakaṃ uppannaṃ hoti.**On one occasion the Sangha was given a cloth.*";
P_HTM[9312]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9313]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pādapuñchaniṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to make it into a doormat.”*";
P_HTM[9314]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū adhotehi pādehi senāsanaṃ akkamanti.**At that time the monks entered the dwellings with dirty feet.*";
P_HTM[9315]="*Senāsanaṃ dussati.**The dwellings became dirty.*";
P_HTM[9316]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9317]="*“Na, bhikkhave, adhotehi pādehi senāsanaṃ akkamitabbaṃ.**“You should not enter a dwelling with dirty feet.*";
P_HTM[9318]="*Yo akkameyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[9319]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū allehi pādehi senāsanaṃ akkamanti.**At that time the monks entered the dwellings with wet feet.*";
P_HTM[9320]="*Senāsanaṃ dussati.**The dwellings became dirty.*";
P_HTM[9321]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9322]="*“Na, bhikkhave, allehi pādehi senāsanaṃ akkamitabbaṃ.**“You should not enter a dwelling with wet feet.*";
P_HTM[9323]="*Yo akkameyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[9324]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū saupāhanā senāsanaṃ akkamanti.**At that time the monks entered the dwellings with their sandals on.*";
P_HTM[9325]="*Senāsanaṃ dussati.**The dwellings became dirty.*";
P_HTM[9326]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9327]="*“Na, bhikkhave, saupāhanena senāsanaṃ akkamitabbaṃ.**“You should not enter a dwelling with your sandals on.*";
P_HTM[9328]="*Yo akkameyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[9329]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū parikammakatāya bhūmiyā niṭṭhubhanti.**At that time the monks spat on treated floors.*";
P_HTM[9330]="*Vaṇṇo dussati.**The coloring was spoiled.*";
P_HTM[9331]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9332]="*“Na, bhikkhave, parikammakatāya bhūmiyā niṭṭhubhitabbaṃ.**“You should not spit on treated floors.*";
P_HTM[9333]="*Yo niṭṭhubheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9334]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kheḷamallakan”ti.**I allow a spittoon.”*";
P_HTM[9335]="*Tena kho pana samayena mañcapādāpi pīṭhapādāpi parikammakataṃ bhūmiṃ vilikhanti.**At that time the legs of the beds and benches scratched the treated floors. The coloring was spoiled.*";
P_HTM[9336]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9337]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, coḷakena paliveṭhetun”ti.**“You should wrap the legs in cloth.”*";
P_HTM[9338]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū parikammakataṃ bhittiṃ apassenti.**At that time the monks were leaning on treated walls.*";
P_HTM[9339]="*Vaṇṇo dussati.**The coloring was spoiled.*";
P_HTM[9340]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9341]="*“Na, bhikkhave, parikammakatā bhitti apassetabbā.**“You should not lean on treated walls.*";
P_HTM[9342]="*Yo apasseyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9343]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, apassenaphalakan”ti.**I allow a leaning board.”*";
P_HTM[9344]="*Apassenaphalakaṃ heṭṭhato bhūmiṃ vilikhati, uparito bhittiñca.**The lower edge of the leaning boards scratched the floor and the upper edge the wall.*";
P_HTM[9345]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9346]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, heṭṭhato ca uparito ca coḷakena paliveṭhetun”ti.**“You should wrap the lower and upper edges in cloth.”*";
P_HTM[9347]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū dhotapādakā nipajjituṃ kukkuccāyanti.**Being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not lie down with washed feet.*";
P_HTM[9348]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9349]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, paccattharitvā nipajjitun”ti.**“You should spread a sheet and then lie down.”*";
P_HTM[9350]="*5. Saṅghabhattādianujānana**3.5 The allowance for meals for the Sangha, etc.*";
P_HTM[9351]="*Atha kho bhagavā āḷaviyaṃ yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena rājagahaṃ tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**When the Buddha had stayed at Āḷavī for as long as he liked, he set out wandering toward Rājagaha.*";
P_HTM[9352]="*Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena rājagahaṃ tadavasari.**When he eventually arrived,*";
P_HTM[9353]="*Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**he stayed in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[9354]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājagahaṃ dubbhikkhaṃ hoti.**At that time Rājagaha was short of food*";
P_HTM[9355]="*Manussā na sakkonti saṅghabhattaṃ kātuṃ;**and people were not able to make meals for the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[9356]="*icchanti uddesabhattaṃ nimantanaṃ salākabhattaṃ pakkhikaṃ uposathikaṃ pāṭipadikaṃ kātuṃ.**Instead they wished to make meals for designated monks, invitational meals, meals for which lots are drawn, half-monthly meals, meals on the observance day, and meals on the day after the observance day.*";
P_HTM[9357]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9358]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, saṅghabhattaṃ uddesabhattaṃ nimantanaṃ salākabhattaṃ pakkhikaṃ uposathikaṃ pāṭipadikan”ti.**“I allow meals for the Sangha, meals for designated monks, invitational meals, meals for which lots are drawn, half-monthly meals, meals on the observance days, and meals on the days after the observance day.”*";
P_HTM[9359]="*6. Bhattuddesakasammuti**3.6 The appointment of a designator of meals*";
P_HTM[9360]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū attano varabhattāni gahetvā lāmakāni bhattāni bhikkhūnaṃ denti.**At that time the monks from the group of six took the best meals for themselves and gave the inferior ones to the other monks.*";
P_HTM[9361]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9362]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgataṃ bhikkhuṃ bhattuddesakaṃ sammannituṃ—**“You should appoint a monk who has five qualities as the designator of meals:*";
P_HTM[9363]="*yo na chandāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na dosāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na mohāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na bhayāgatiṃ gaccheyya, uddiṭṭhānuddiṭṭhañca jāneyya.**he is not swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear, and he knows what has and has not been designated.*";
P_HTM[9364]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sammannitabbo.**And he should be appointed like this.*";
P_HTM[9365]="*Paṭhamaṃ bhikkhu yācitabbo, yācitvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**First a monk should be asked, and then a competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[9366]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[9367]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ bhattuddesakaṃ sammanneyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should appoint monk so-and-so as designator of meals.*";
P_HTM[9368]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[9369]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[9370]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ bhattuddesakaṃ sammannati.**The Sangha appoints monk so-and-so as designator of meals.*";
P_HTM[9371]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno bhattuddesakassa sammuti, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of appointing monk so-and-so as designator of meals should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[9372]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[9373]="*Sammato saṅghena itthannāmo bhikkhu bhattuddesako.**The Sangha has appointed monk so-and-so as designator of meals.*";
P_HTM[9374]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[9375]="*Atha kho bhattuddesakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The monks who were designator of meals thought,*";
P_HTM[9376]="*“kathaṃ nu kho bhattaṃ uddisitabban”ti?**“How should we designate the meals?”*";
P_HTM[9377]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9378]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, salākāya vā paṭṭikāya vā upanibandhitvā opuñjitvā bhattaṃ uddisitun”ti.**“You should mark the tickets and make a heap of them, and then designate the meals.”*";
P_HTM[9379]="*7. Senāsanapaññāpakādisammuti**3.7 The appointment of assigners of dwellings, etc.*";
P_HTM[9380]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa senāsanapaññāpako na hoti …pe…**At that time there was no assigner of dwellings …*";
P_HTM[9381]="*bhaṇḍāgāriko na hoti …pe…**no storeman …*";
P_HTM[9382]="*cīvarappaṭiggāhako na hoti …pe…**no receiver of robe-cloth …*";
P_HTM[9383]="*cīvarabhājako na hoti …pe…**no distributor of robe-cloth …*";
P_HTM[9384]="*yāgubhājako na hoti …pe…**no distributor of rice porridge …*";
P_HTM[9385]="*phalabhājako na hoti …pe…**no distributor of fruit …*";
P_HTM[9386]="*khajjakabhājako na hoti.**no distributor of fresh foods.*";
P_HTM[9387]="*Khajjakaṃ abhājiyamānaṃ nassati.**Because it was not distributed, the fresh food perished.*";
P_HTM[9388]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9389]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgataṃ bhikkhuṃ khajjakabhājakaṃ sammannituṃ—**“You should appoint a monk who has five qualities as the distributor of fresh foods:*";
P_HTM[9390]="*yo na chandāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na dosāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na mohāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na bhayāgatiṃ gaccheyya, bhājitābhājitañca jāneyya.**he is not swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear, and he knows what has and has not been distributed.*";
P_HTM[9391]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sammannitabbo.**And he should be appointed like this.*";
P_HTM[9392]="*Paṭhamaṃ bhikkhu yācitabbo, yācitvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**First a monk should be asked, and then a competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[9393]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[9394]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ khajjakabhājakaṃ sammanneyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should appoint monk so-and-so as distributor of fresh foods.*";
P_HTM[9395]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[9396]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[9397]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ khajjakabhājakaṃ sammannati.**The Sangha appoints monk so-and-so as distributor of fresh foods.*";
P_HTM[9398]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno khajjakabhājakassa sammuti, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of appointing monk so-and-so as distributor of fresh foods should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[9399]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[9400]="*Sammato saṅghena itthannāmo bhikkhu khajjakabhājako.**The Sangha has appointed monk so-and-so as distributor of fresh foods.*";
P_HTM[9401]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[9402]="*8. Appamattakavissajjakasammuti**3.8 The appointment of distributors of minor requisites*";
P_HTM[9403]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa bhaṇḍāgāre appamattako parikkhāro uppanno hoti.**At that time there were minor requisites in the storeroom.*";
P_HTM[9404]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9405]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgataṃ bhikkhuṃ appamattakavissajjakaṃ sammannituṃ—**“You should appoint a monk who has five qualities as the distributor of minor requisites:*";
P_HTM[9406]="*yo na chandāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na dosāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na mohāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na bhayāgatiṃ gaccheyya, vissajjitāvissajjitañca jāneyya.**he is not swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear, and he knows what has and has not been distributed.*";
P_HTM[9407]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sammannitabbo.**And he should be appointed like this.*";
P_HTM[9408]="*Paṭhamaṃ bhikkhu yācitabbo, yācitvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**First a monk should be asked, and then a competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[9409]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[9410]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ appamattakavissajjakaṃ sammanneyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should appoint monk so-and-so as distributor of minor requisites.*";
P_HTM[9411]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[9412]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[9413]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ appamattakavissajjakaṃ sammannati.**The Sangha appoints monk so-and-so as distributor of minor requisites.*";
P_HTM[9414]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno appamattakavissajjakassa sammuti, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of appointing monk so-and-so as distributor of minor requisites should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[9415]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[9416]="*Sammato saṅghena itthannāmo bhikkhu appamattakavissajjako.**The Sangha has appointed monk so-and-so as distributor of minor requisites.*";
P_HTM[9417]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[9418]="*Tena appamattakavissajjakena bhikkhunā ekā sūci dātabbā, satthakaṃ dātabbaṃ, upāhanā dātabbā, kāyabandhanaṃ dātabbaṃ, aṃsabaddhako dātabbo, parissāvanaṃ dātabbaṃ, dhammakaraṇo dātabbo, kusi dātabbā, aḍḍhakusi dātabbā, maṇḍalaṃ dātabbaṃ, aḍḍhamaṇḍalaṃ dātabbaṃ, anuvāto dātabbo, paribhaṇḍaṃ dātabbaṃ.**The monk who is the distributor of minor requisites should give out, one by one: needles, knives, sandals, belts, shoulder straps, water filters, water strainers; and robe material for long inter-panel strips, short inter-panel strips, large panels, medium-sized panels, lengthwise borders, and crosswise borders.*";
P_HTM[9419]="*Sace hoti saṅghassa sappi vā telaṃ vā madhu vā phāṇitaṃ vā, sakiṃ paṭisāyituṃ dātabbaṃ.**If the Sangha has ghee, oil, honey, or syrup, he should give it out for a single use.*";
P_HTM[9420]="*Sace punapi attho hoti, punapi dātabbaṃ.**If it is needed again, he should give it out again.*";
P_HTM[9421]="*9. Sāṭiyaggāhāpakādisammuti**3.9 The appointment of distributors of rainy-season bathing cloths, etc.*";
P_HTM[9422]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa sāṭiyaggāhāpako na hoti …pe…**At that time there was no distributor of rainy-season bathing cloths …*";
P_HTM[9423]="*pattaggāhāpako na hoti …pe…**no distributor of almsbowls …*";
P_HTM[9424]="*ārāmikapesako na hoti …pe…**no supervisor of monastery workers …*";
P_HTM[9425]="*sāmaṇerapesako na hoti.**no supervisor of novice monks.*";
P_HTM[9426]="*Sāmaṇerā apesiyamānā kammaṃ na karonti.**Not being supervised, the novice monks didn’t do their work.*";
P_HTM[9427]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9428]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgataṃ bhikkhuṃ sāmaṇerapesakaṃ sammannituṃ—**“You should appoint a monk who has five qualities as the supervisor of novice monks:*";
P_HTM[9429]="*yo na chandāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na dosāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na mohāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na bhayāgatiṃ gaccheyya, pesitāpesitañca jāneyya.**he is not swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear, and he knows who is and is not supervised.*";
P_HTM[9430]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sammannitabbo.**And he should be appointed like this.*";
P_HTM[9431]="*Paṭhamaṃ bhikkhu yācitabbo, yācitvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**First a monk should be asked, and then a competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[9432]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[9433]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ sāmaṇerapesakaṃ sammanneyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should appoint monk so-and-so as supervisor of novice monks.*";
P_HTM[9434]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[9435]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[9436]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ sāmaṇerapesakaṃ sammannati.**The Sangha appoints monk so-and-so as supervisor of novice monks.*";
P_HTM[9437]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno sāmaṇerapesakassa sammuti, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of appointing monk so-and-so as supervisor of novice monks should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[9438]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[9439]="*Sammato saṅghena itthannāmo bhikkhu sāmaṇerapesako.**The Sangha has appointed monk so-and-so as supervisor of novice monks.*";
P_HTM[9440]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[9441]="*Tatiyabhāṇavāro niṭṭhito.**The third section for recitation is finished.*";
P_HTM[9442]="*Senāsanakkhandhako chaṭṭho.**The sixth chapter on dwellings is finished.*";
P_HTM[9443]="*Tassuddānaṃ* **";
P_HTM[9444]="*Vihāraṃ buddhaseṭṭhena,* **";
P_HTM[9445]="*apaññattaṃ tadā ahu;* **";
P_HTM[9446]="*Tahaṃ tahaṃ nikkhamanti,* **";
P_HTM[9447]="*vāsā te jinasāvakā.* **";
P_HTM[9448]="*Seṭṭhī gahapati disvā,* **";
P_HTM[9449]="*bhikkhūnaṃ idamabravi;* **";
P_HTM[9450]="*Kārāpeyyaṃ vaseyyātha,* **";
P_HTM[9451]="*paṭipucchiṃsu nāyakaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9452]="*Vihāraṃ aḍḍhayogañca,* **";
P_HTM[9453]="*pāsādaṃ hammiyaṃ guhaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[9454]="*Pañcaleṇaṃ anuññāsi,* **";
P_HTM[9455]="*vihāre seṭṭhi kārayi.* **";
P_HTM[9456]="*Jano vihāraṃ kāreti,* **";
P_HTM[9457]="*akavāṭaṃ asaṃvutaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[9458]="*Kavāṭaṃ piṭṭhasaṅghāṭaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[9459]="*udukkhalañca uttari.* **";
P_HTM[9460]="*Āviñchanacchiddaṃ rajjuṃ,* **";
P_HTM[9461]="*vaṭṭiñca kapisīsakaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[9462]="*Sūcighaṭitāḷacchiddaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[9463]="*lohakaṭṭhavisāṇakaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9464]="*Yantakaṃ sūcikañceva,* **";
P_HTM[9465]="*chadanaṃ ullittāvalittaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[9466]="*Vedijālasalākañca,* **";
P_HTM[9467]="*cakkali santharena ca.* **";
P_HTM[9468]="*Miḍḍhi bidalamañcañca,* **";
P_HTM[9469]="*sosānikamasārako;* **";
P_HTM[9470]="*Bundikuḷirapādañca,* **";
P_HTM[9471]="*āhaccāsandi uccake.* **";
P_HTM[9472]="*Sattaṅgo ca bhaddapīṭhaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[9473]="*pīṭhakeḷakapādakaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[9474]="*Āmalāphalakā kocchā,* **";
P_HTM[9475]="*palālapīṭhameva ca.* **";
P_HTM[9476]="*Uccāhipaṭipādakā,* **";
P_HTM[9477]="*aṭṭhaṅguli ca pādakā;* **";
P_HTM[9478]="*Suttaṃ aṭṭhapadaṃ coḷaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[9479]="*tūlikaṃ aḍḍhakāyikaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9480]="*Giraggo bhisiyo cāpi,* **";
P_HTM[9481]="*dussaṃ senāsanampi ca;* **";
P_HTM[9482]="*Onaddhaṃ heṭṭhā patati,* **";
P_HTM[9483]="*uppāṭetvā haranti ca.* **";
P_HTM[9484]="*Bhattiñca hatthabhattiñca,* **";
P_HTM[9485]="*anuññāsi tathāgato;* **";
P_HTM[9486]="*Titthiyā vihāre cāpi,* **";
P_HTM[9487]="*thusaṃ saṇhañca mattikā.* **";
P_HTM[9488]="*Ikkāsaṃ pāṇikaṃ kuṇḍaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[9489]="*sāsapaṃ sitthatelakaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[9490]="*Ussanne paccuddharituṃ,* **";
P_HTM[9491]="*pharusaṃ gaṇḍumattikaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9492]="*Ikkāsaṃ paṭibhānañca,* **";
P_HTM[9493]="*nīcā cayo ca āruhaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[9494]="*Paripatanti āḷakā,* **";
P_HTM[9495]="*aḍḍhakuṭṭaṃ tayo puna.* **";
P_HTM[9496]="*Khuddake kuṭṭapādo ca,* **";
P_HTM[9497]="*ovassati saraṃ khilaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[9498]="*Cīvaravaṃsaṃ rajjuñca,* **";
P_HTM[9499]="*āḷindaṃ kiṭikena ca.* **";
P_HTM[9500]="*Ālambanaṃ tiṇacuṇṇaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[9501]="*heṭṭhāmagge nayaṃ kare;* **";
P_HTM[9502]="*Ajjhokāse otappati,* **";
P_HTM[9503]="*sālaṃ heṭṭhā ca bhājanaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9504]="*Vihāro koṭṭhako ceva,* **";
P_HTM[9505]="*pariveṇaggisālakaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[9506]="*Ārāme ca puna koṭṭhe,* **";
P_HTM[9507]="*heṭṭhaññeva nayaṃ kare.* **";
P_HTM[9508]="*Sudhaṃ anāthapiṇḍi ca,* **";
P_HTM[9509]="*saddho sītavanaṃ agā;* **";
P_HTM[9510]="*Diṭṭhadhammo nimantesi,* **";
P_HTM[9511]="*saha saṅghena nāyakaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9512]="*Āṇāpesantarāmagge,* **";
P_HTM[9513]="*ārāmaṃ kārayī gaṇo;* **";
P_HTM[9514]="*Vesāliyaṃ navakammaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[9515]="*purato ca pariggahi.* **";
P_HTM[9516]="*Ko arahati bhattagge,* **";
P_HTM[9517]="*tittirañca avandiyā;* **";
P_HTM[9518]="*Pariggahitantaragharā,* **";
P_HTM[9519]="*tūlo sāvatthi osari.* **";
P_HTM[9520]="*Patiṭṭhāpesi ārāmaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[9521]="*bhattagge ca kolāhalaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[9522]="*Gilānā varaseyyā ca,* **";
P_HTM[9523]="*lesā sattarasā tahiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9524]="*Kena nu kho kathaṃ nu kho,* **";
P_HTM[9525]="*vihāraggena bhājayi;* **";
P_HTM[9526]="*Pariveṇaṃ anubhāgañca,* **";
P_HTM[9527]="*akāmā bhāgaṃ no dade.* **";
P_HTM[9528]="*Nissīmaṃ sabbakālañca,* **";
P_HTM[9529]="*gāhā senāsane tayo;* **";
P_HTM[9530]="*Upanando ca vaṇṇesi,* **";
P_HTM[9531]="*ṭhitakā samakāsanā.* **";
P_HTM[9532]="*Samānāsanikā bhindiṃsu,* **";
P_HTM[9533]="*tivaggā ca duvaggikaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[9534]="*Asamānāsanikā dīghaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[9535]="*sāḷindaṃ paribhuñjituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9536]="*Ayyikā ca avidūre,* **";
P_HTM[9537]="*bhājitañca kīṭāgire;* **";
P_HTM[9538]="*Āḷavī piṇḍakakuṭṭehi,* **";
P_HTM[9539]="*dvāraaggaḷavaṭṭikā.* **";
P_HTM[9540]="*Ālokasetakāḷañca,* **";
P_HTM[9541]="*geruchādanabandhanā;* **";
P_HTM[9542]="*Bhaṇḍikhaṇḍaparibhaṇḍaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[9543]="*vīsa tiṃsā ca kālikā.* **";
P_HTM[9544]="*Osite akataṃ vippaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[9545]="*khudde chappañcavassikaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[9546]="*Aḍḍhayoge ca sattaṭṭha,* **";
P_HTM[9547]="*mahalle dasa dvādasa.* **";
P_HTM[9548]="*Sabbaṃ vihāraṃ ekassa,* **";
P_HTM[9549]="*aññaṃ vāsenti saṅghikaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[9550]="*Nissīmaṃ sabbakālañca,* **";
P_HTM[9551]="*pakkami vibbhamanti ca.* **";
P_HTM[9552]="*Kālañca sāmaṇerañca,* **";
P_HTM[9553]="*sikkhāpaccakkhaantimaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[9554]="*Ummattakhittacittā ca,* **";
P_HTM[9555]="*vedanāpattidassanā.* **";
P_HTM[9556]="*Appaṭikammadiṭṭhiyā,* **";
P_HTM[9557]="*paṇḍakā theyyatitthiyā;* **";
P_HTM[9558]="*Tiracchānamātupitu,* **";
P_HTM[9559]="*arahantā ca dūsakā.* **";
P_HTM[9560]="*Bhedakā lohituppādā,* **";
P_HTM[9561]="*ubhato cāpi byañjanakā;* **";
P_HTM[9562]="*Mā saṅghassa parihāyi,* **";
P_HTM[9563]="*kammaṃ aññassa dātave.* **";
P_HTM[9564]="*Vippakate ca aññassa,* **";
P_HTM[9565]="*kate tasseva pakkame;* **";
P_HTM[9566]="*Vibbhamati kālaṅkato,* **";
P_HTM[9567]="*sāmaṇero ca jāyati.* **";
P_HTM[9568]="*Paccakkhāto ca sikkhāya,* **";
P_HTM[9569]="*antimajjhāpannako yadi;* **";
P_HTM[9570]="*Saṅghova sāmiko hoti,* **";
P_HTM[9571]="*ummattakhittavedanā.* **";
P_HTM[9572]="*Adassanāppaṭikamme,* **";
P_HTM[9573]="*diṭṭhi tasseva hoti taṃ;* **";
P_HTM[9574]="*Paṇḍako theyyatitthī ca,* **";
P_HTM[9575]="*tiracchānamātupettikaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9576]="*Ghātako dūsako cāpi,* **";
P_HTM[9577]="*bhedalohitabyañjanā;* **";
P_HTM[9578]="*Paṭijānāti yadi so,* **";
P_HTM[9579]="*saṅghova hoti sāmiko.* **";
P_HTM[9580]="*Harantaññatra kukkuccaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[9581]="*undriyati ca kambalaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[9582]="*Dussañca cammacakkalī,* **";
P_HTM[9583]="*coḷakaṃ akkamanti ca.* **";
P_HTM[9584]="*Allā upāhanāniṭṭhu,* **";
P_HTM[9585]="*likhanti apassenti ca;* **";
P_HTM[9586]="*Apassenaṃ likhateva,* **";
P_HTM[9587]="*dhotapaccattharena ca.* **";
P_HTM[9588]="*Rājagahe na sakkonti,* **";
P_HTM[9589]="*lāmakaṃ bhattuddesakaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[9590]="*Kathaṃ nu kho paññāpakaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[9591]="*bhaṇḍāgārikasammuti.* **";
P_HTM[9592]="*Paṭiggāhabhājako cāpi,* **";
P_HTM[9593]="*yāgu ca phalabhājako;* **";
P_HTM[9594]="*Khajjakabhājako ceva,* **";
P_HTM[9595]="*appamattakavissajje.* **";
P_HTM[9596]="*Sāṭiyaggāhāpako ceva,* **";
P_HTM[9597]="*tatheva pattaggāhako;* **";
P_HTM[9598]="*Ārāmikasāmaṇera,* **";
P_HTM[9599]="*pesakassa ca sammuti.* **";
P_HTM[9600]="*Sabbābhibhū lokavidū,**He has conquered all and knows the world,*";
P_HTM[9601]="*hitacitto vināyako;**The Leader intent on what’s beneficial:*";
P_HTM[9602]="*Leṇatthañca sukhatthañca,**It’s for the sake of shelter and happiness,*";
P_HTM[9603]="*jhāyituñca vipassitunti.**To attain absorption and to see clearly.*";
P_HTM[9604]="*Senāsanakkhandhako niṭṭhito.**The chapter on dwellings is finished.*";
P_HTM[9605]="*7. Saṅghabhedakakkhandhaka **7.  The chapter on schism in the Sangha *";
P_HTM[9606]="*1. Chasakyapabbajjākathā**1.1 The account of the going forth of the six Sakyans*";
P_HTM[9607]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā anupiyāyaṃ viharati, anupiyaṃ nāma mallānaṃ nigamo.**At one time the Buddha was staying at the Mallian town of Anupiyā.*";
P_HTM[9608]="*Tena kho pana samayena abhiññātā abhiññātā sakyakumārā bhagavantaṃ pabbajitaṃ anupabbajanti.**At this time a number of well-known young Sakyans had followed the Buddha in going forth.*";
P_HTM[9609]="*Tena kho pana samayena mahānāmo ca sakko anuruddho ca sakko dvebhātikā honti.**The Sakyans Mahānāma and Anuruddha were brothers.*";
P_HTM[9610]="*Anuruddho sakko sukhumālo hoti.**Anuruddha had been brought up in great comfort.*";
P_HTM[9611]="*Tassa tayo pāsādā honti—**He had three stilt houses:*";
P_HTM[9612]="*eko hemantiko, eko gimhiko, eko vassiko.**one for the winter, one for the summer, and one for the rainy season.*";
P_HTM[9613]="*So vassike pāsāde cattāro māse nippurisehi tūriyehi paricārayamāno na heṭṭhāpāsādaṃ orohati.**He spent the four months of the rainy season in the rainy-season house, attended on only by female musicians, never descending from that house.*";
P_HTM[9614]="*Atha kho mahānāmassa sakkassa etadahosi—**Mahānāma thought,*";
P_HTM[9615]="*“etarahi kho abhiññātā abhiññātā sakyakumārā bhagavantaṃ pabbajitaṃ anupabbajanti.**“A number of well-known young Sakyans have just followed the Buddha in going forth,*";
P_HTM[9616]="*Amhākañca pana kulā natthi koci agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito.**but no one from our household.*";
P_HTM[9617]="*Yannūnāhaṃ vā pabbajeyyaṃ, anuruddho vā”ti.**Why donʼt Anuruddha or I go forth?”*";
P_HTM[9618]="*Atha kho mahānāmo sakko yena anuruddho sakko tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā anuruddhaṃ sakkaṃ etadavoca—**He then went to Anuruddha and told him what he had thought.*";
P_HTM[9619]="*“etarahi, tāta anuruddha, abhiññātā abhiññātā sakyakumārā bhagavantaṃ pabbajitaṃ anupabbajanti.* **";
P_HTM[9620]="*Amhākañca pana kulā natthi koci agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito.* **";
P_HTM[9621]="*Tena hi tvaṃ vā pabbaja, ahaṃ vā pabbajissāmī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[9622]="*“Ahaṃ kho sukhumālo, nāhaṃ sakkomi agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajituṃ.**Anuruddha replied, “I’ve been brought up in great comfort; I’m not able to go forth.*";
P_HTM[9623]="*Tvaṃ pabbajāhī”ti.**You go forth.”*";
P_HTM[9624]="*“Ehi kho te, tāta anuruddha, gharāvāsatthaṃ anusāsissāmi.**“Come then, and I’ll teach you the affairs of the household life.*";
P_HTM[9625]="*Paṭhamaṃ khettaṃ kasāpetabbaṃ.**First you must plow the fields,*";
P_HTM[9626]="*Kasāpetvā vapāpetabbaṃ.**then sow the seeds,*";
P_HTM[9627]="*Vapāpetvā udakaṃ abhinetabbaṃ.**irrigate,*";
P_HTM[9628]="*Udakaṃ abhinetvā udakaṃ ninnetabbaṃ.**and drain,*";
P_HTM[9629]="*Udakaṃ ninnetvā niddhāpetabbaṃ.**and then weed.*";
P_HTM[9630]="*Niddhāpetvā lavāpetabbaṃ.**Next you must cut the harvest,*";
P_HTM[9631]="*Lavāpetvā ubbāhāpetabbaṃ.**gather it together,*";
P_HTM[9632]="*Ubbāhāpetvā puñjaṃ kārāpetabbaṃ.**and make sheaves.*";
P_HTM[9633]="*Puñjaṃ kārāpetvā maddāpetabbaṃ.**You must then thresh it,*";
P_HTM[9634]="*Maddāpetvā palālāni uddharāpetabbāni.**remove the straw*";
P_HTM[9635]="*Palālāni uddharāpetvā bhusikā uddharāpetabbā.**and husk,*";
P_HTM[9636]="*Bhusikaṃ uddharāpetvā opunāpetabbaṃ.**and then winnow it*";
P_HTM[9637]="*Opunāpetvā atiharāpetabbaṃ.**before you bring it into storage.*";
P_HTM[9638]="*Atiharāpetvā āyatimpi vassaṃ evameva kātabbaṃ, āyatimpi vassaṃ evameva kātabban”ti.**And next year you must do the same, and the next.”*";
P_HTM[9639]="*“Na kammā khīyanti?**“But does the work never stop?*";
P_HTM[9640]="*Na kammānaṃ anto paññāyati?**I can’t see any end to it.*";
P_HTM[9641]="*Kadā kammā khīyissanti?* **";
P_HTM[9642]="*Kadā kammānaṃ anto paññāyissati?* **";
P_HTM[9643]="*Kadā mayaṃ appossukkā pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappitā samaṅgībhūtā paricāressāmā”ti?**When can you enjoy yourself with worldly pleasures, free from bother?”*";
P_HTM[9644]="*“Na hi, tāta anuruddha, kammā khīyanti.**“The work doesn’t stop*";
P_HTM[9645]="*Na kammānaṃ anto paññāyati.**and you won’t see any end of it.*";
P_HTM[9646]="*Akhīṇeva kamme pitaro ca pitāmahā ca kālaṅkatā”ti.**While the work was still unfinished, our fathers and grandfathers have all died.”*";
P_HTM[9647]="*“Tena hi tvaññeva gharāvāsatthena upajānāhi.**“Well then, you go ahead with the affairs of the household life.*";
P_HTM[9648]="*Ahaṃ agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissāmī”ti.**I’ll go forth into homelessness.”*";
P_HTM[9649]="*Atha kho anuruddho sakko yena mātā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā mātaraṃ etadavoca—**Anuruddha then went to his mother and said,*";
P_HTM[9650]="*“icchāmahaṃ, amma, agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajituṃ.**“Mum, I wish to go forth into homelessness.*";
P_HTM[9651]="*Anujānāhi maṃ agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti.**Please allow me.”*";
P_HTM[9652]="*Evaṃ vutte, anuruddhassa sakkassa mātā anuruddhaṃ sakkaṃ etadavoca—* **";
P_HTM[9653]="*“tumhe kho me, tāta anuruddha, dve puttā piyā manāpā appaṭikūlā.**“Both of you, Anuruddha, my two sons, are dear and beloved to me.*";
P_HTM[9654]="*Maraṇenapi vo akāmakā vinā bhavissāmi.**Even if you died I would lose you against my wishes.*";
P_HTM[9655]="*Kiṃ panāhaṃ tumhe jīvante anujānissāmi agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti?**So how can I allow you to go forth into homelessness while you’re still living?”*";
P_HTM[9656]="*Dutiyampi kho …pe…**A second time Anuruddha asked the same question and got the same reply.*";
P_HTM[9657]="*tatiyampi kho anuruddho sakko mātaraṃ etadavoca—**He then asked a third time.*";
P_HTM[9658]="*“icchāmahaṃ, amma, agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9659]="*Anujānāhi maṃ agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[9660]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhaddiyo sakyarājā sakyānaṃ rajjaṃ kāreti.**At that time the Sakyans were ruled by King Bhaddiya,*";
P_HTM[9661]="*So ca anuruddhassa sakkassa sahāyo hoti.**who was a friend of Anuruddha’s.*";
P_HTM[9662]="*Atha kho anuruddhassa sakkassa mātā—**Anuruddha’s mother considered this*";
P_HTM[9663]="*“ayaṃ kho bhaddiyo sakyarājā sakyānaṃ rajjaṃ kāreti;* **";
P_HTM[9664]="*anuruddhassa sakkassa sahāyo;* **";
P_HTM[9665]="*so na ussahati agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitun”ti—**and thought, “Bhaddiya won’t be able to go forth into homelessness.”*";
P_HTM[9666]="*anuruddhaṃ sakkaṃ etadavoca—**And she said to Anuruddha,*";
P_HTM[9667]="*“sace, tāta anuruddha, bhaddiyo sakyarājā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati, evaṃ tvampi pabbajāhī”ti.**“If Bhaddiya the King of the Sakyans goes forth, then you too may go forth.”*";
P_HTM[9668]="*Atha kho anuruddho sakko yena bhaddiyo sakyarājā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhaddiyaṃ sakyarājānaṃ etadavoca—**Anuruddha then went to King Baddiya and said,*";
P_HTM[9669]="*“mama kho, samma, pabbajjā tava paṭibaddhā”ti.**“My going forth depends on yours.”*";
P_HTM[9670]="*“Sace te, samma, pabbajjā mama paṭibaddhā vā appaṭibaddhā vā sā hotu, ahaṃ tayā;**“Don’t worry about whether your going forth depends on mine or not. I’m with you.*";
P_HTM[9671]="*yathā sukhaṃ pabbajāhī”ti.**So just go forth when you like.”*";
P_HTM[9672]="*“Ehi, samma, ubho agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissāmā”ti.**“Come, let’s go forth together.”*";
P_HTM[9673]="*“Nāhaṃ, samma, sakkomi agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitunti.**“I’m not able to go forth.*";
P_HTM[9674]="*Yaṃ te sakkā aññaṃ mayā kātuṃ, kyāhaṃ karissāmi.**I’m not able to do what you do. What can I do?*";
P_HTM[9675]="*Tvaṃ pabbajāhī”ti.**You go forth.”*";
P_HTM[9676]="*“Mātā kho maṃ, samma, evamāha—**“My mother told me*";
P_HTM[9677]="*‘sace, tāta anuruddha, bhaddiyo sakyarājā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati, evaṃ tvampi pabbajāhī’”ti.**that I may go forth only if you go forth.*";
P_HTM[9678]="*“Bhāsitā kho pana te, samma, esā vācā.**And then you said,*";
P_HTM[9679]="*Sace te, samma, pabbajjā mama paṭibaddhā vā, appaṭibaddhā vā sā hotu, ahaṃ tayā;**‘Don’t worry about whether your going forth depends on mine or not. I’m with you.*";
P_HTM[9680]="*yathā sukhaṃ pabbajāhī”ti.**So just go forth when you like.’*";
P_HTM[9681]="*“Ehi, samma, ubho agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissāmā”ti.**So come, let’s go forth together.”*";
P_HTM[9682]="*Tena kho pana samayena manussā saccavādino honti, saccapaṭiññā.**At that time people spoke the truth,*";
P_HTM[9683]="*Atha kho bhaddiyo sakyarājā anuruddhaṃ sakkaṃ etadavoca—**and so Bhaddiya said to Anuruddha,*";
P_HTM[9684]="*“āgamehi, samma, sattavassāni.**“Please wait seven years.*";
P_HTM[9685]="*Sattannaṃ vassānaṃ accayena ubho agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissāmā”ti.**Then we’ll go forth together.”*";
P_HTM[9686]="*“Aticiraṃ, samma, sattavassāni.**“That’s too long.*";
P_HTM[9687]="*Nāhaṃ sakkomi sattavassāni āgametun”ti.**I’m not able to wait for seven years.”*";
P_HTM[9688]="*“Āgamehi, samma, chavassāni …pe…**“Then wait six years …*";
P_HTM[9689]="*pañcavassāni …**five years …*";
P_HTM[9690]="*cattāri vassāni …**four years …*";
P_HTM[9691]="*tīṇi vassāni …**three years …*";
P_HTM[9692]="*dve vassāni …**two years …*";
P_HTM[9693]="*ekaṃ vassaṃ.**one year,*";
P_HTM[9694]="*Ekassa vassassa accayena ubho agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissāmā”ti.**and we’ll go forth together.”*";
P_HTM[9695]="*“Aticiraṃ, samma, ekavassaṃ.**“That’s too long.*";
P_HTM[9696]="*Nāhaṃ sakkomi ekaṃ vassaṃ āgametun”ti.**I’m not able to wait for one year.”*";
P_HTM[9697]="*“Āgamehi, samma, sattamāse.**“Then wait seven months,*";
P_HTM[9698]="*Sattannaṃ māsānaṃ accayena ubhopi agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissāmā”ti.**and we’ll go forth together.”*";
P_HTM[9699]="*“Aticiraṃ, samma, sattamāsā.**“That’s too long.*";
P_HTM[9700]="*Nāhaṃ sakkomi sattamāse āgametun”ti.**I’m not able to wait for seven months.”*";
P_HTM[9701]="*“Āgamehi, samma, cha māse …pe…**“Then wait six months …*";
P_HTM[9702]="*pañca māse …**five months …*";
P_HTM[9703]="*cattāro māse …**four months …*";
P_HTM[9704]="*tayo māse …**three months …*";
P_HTM[9705]="*dve māse …**two months …*";
P_HTM[9706]="*ekaṃ māsaṃ …**one month …*";
P_HTM[9707]="*aḍḍhamāsaṃ.**half a month,*";
P_HTM[9708]="*Aḍḍhamāsassa accayena ubhopi agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissāmā”ti.**and we’ll go forth together.”*";
P_HTM[9709]="*“Aticiraṃ, samma, aḍḍhamāso.**“That’s too long.*";
P_HTM[9710]="*Nāhaṃ sakkomi aḍḍhamāsaṃ āgametun”ti.**I’m not able to wait for half a month.”*";
P_HTM[9711]="*“Āgamehi, samma, sattāhaṃ yāvāhaṃ putte ca bhātaro ca rajjaṃ niyyādemī”ti.**“Then wait seven days, while I hand over the rulership to my sons and brothers.”*";
P_HTM[9712]="*“Na ciraṃ, samma, sattāho, āgamessāmī”ti.**“Seven days isn’t long. I’ll wait.”*";
P_HTM[9713]="*Atha kho bhaddiyo ca sakyarājā anuruddho ca ānando ca bhagu ca kimilo ca devadatto ca, upālikappakena sattamā, yathā pure caturaṅginiyā senāya uyyānabhūmiṃ niyyanti, evameva caturaṅginiyā senāya niyyiṃsu.**Soon afterwards King Bhaddiya, Anuruddha, Ānanda, Bhagu, Kimila, and Devadatta, with the barber Upāli as the seventh, went out to the park with the fourfold army, just as they used to.*";
P_HTM[9714]="*Te dūraṃ gantvā senaṃ nivattāpetvā paravisayaṃ okkamitvā ābharaṇaṃ omuñcitvā uttarāsaṅgena bhaṇḍikaṃ bandhitvā upāliṃ kappakaṃ etadavocuṃ—**After going a good distance, they turned back the army. They then entered a foreign territory, removed their ornaments, bound them in a bundle with an upper robe, and said to Upāli,*";
P_HTM[9715]="*“handa, bhaṇe upāli, nivattassu;**“Now turn back, Upāli.*";
P_HTM[9716]="*alaṃ te ettakaṃ jīvikāyā”ti.**This is enough for you to live on.”*";
P_HTM[9717]="*Atha kho upālissa kappakassa nivattantassa etadahosi—**As Upāli was returning, he thought,*";
P_HTM[9718]="*“caṇḍā kho sākiyā;**“The Sakyans are temperamental.*";
P_HTM[9719]="*iminā kumārā nippātitāti ghātāpeyyumpi maṃ.**Thinking that I’m responsible for the departure of these young men, they might have me killed.*";
P_HTM[9720]="*Ime hi nāma sakyakumārā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissanti.**Now, if these young Sakyans are going forth into homelessness,*";
P_HTM[9721]="*Kimaṅgaṃ panāhan”ti.**why shouldn’t I?”*";
P_HTM[9722]="*Bhaṇḍikaṃ muñcitvā taṃ bhaṇḍaṃ rukkhe ālaggetvā “yo passati, dinnaṃyeva haratū”ti vatvā yena te sakyakumārā tenupasaṅkami.**Undoing the bundle, he hung the goods from a tree, saying, “Whoever sees this may take it as given.” And he returned to the young Sakyans.*";
P_HTM[9723]="*Addasāsuṃ kho te sakyakumārā upāliṃ kappakaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**Seeing Upāli coming,*";
P_HTM[9724]="*Disvāna upāliṃ kappakaṃ etadavocuṃ—**they said to him,*";
P_HTM[9725]="*“kissa, bhaṇe upāli, nivattesī”ti?**“Why are you coming back, Upāli?”*";
P_HTM[9726]="*“Idha me, ayyaputtā, nivattantassa etadahosi—**And he told what he had done.*";
P_HTM[9727]="*‘caṇḍā kho sākiyā;* **";
P_HTM[9728]="*iminā kumārā nippātitāti ghātāpeyyumpi maṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9729]="*Ime hi nāma sakyakumārā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissanti.* **";
P_HTM[9730]="*Kimaṅgaṃ panāhan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[9731]="*So kho ahaṃ, ayyaputtā, bhaṇḍikaṃ muñcitvā taṃ bhaṇḍaṃ rukkhe ālaggetvā ‘yo passati, dinnaññeva haratū’ti vatvā tatomhi paṭinivatto”ti.* **";
P_HTM[9732]="*“Suṭṭhu, bhaṇe upāli, akāsi yampi na nivatto.**“You have done the right thing.*";
P_HTM[9733]="*Caṇḍā kho sākiyā;**The Sakyans are indeed temperamental.*";
P_HTM[9734]="*iminā kumārā nippātitāti ghātāpeyyumpi tan”ti.**Thinking that you were responsible for our departure, they might have killed you.”*";
P_HTM[9735]="*Atha kho sakyakumārā upāliṃ kappakaṃ ādāya yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu.**Then the young Sakyans, taking Upāli with them, went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[9736]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te sakyakumārā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ—**and said,*";
P_HTM[9737]="*“mayaṃ, bhante, sākiyā nāma mānassino.**“Venerable Sir, we Sakyans are proud.*";
P_HTM[9738]="*Ayaṃ, bhante, upāli kappako amhākaṃ dīgharattaṃ paricārako.**This barber Upāli has been serving us for a long time.*";
P_HTM[9739]="*Imaṃ bhagavā paṭhamaṃ pabbājetu.**Please let him go forth first.*";
P_HTM[9740]="*Imassa mayaṃ abhivādanapaccuṭṭhānaañjalikammasāmīcikammaṃ karissāma.**We will then bow down to him, rise up for him, raise our joined palms to him, and do acts of respect toward him.*";
P_HTM[9741]="*Evaṃ amhākaṃ sākiyānaṃ sākiyamāno nimmānāyissatī”ti.**In this way our Sakyan pride will be subdued.”*";
P_HTM[9742]="*Atha kho bhagavā upāliṃ kappakaṃ paṭhamaṃ pabbājesi, pacchā te sakyakumāre.**And the Buddha had Upāli go forth first, and afterwards the young Sakyans.*";
P_HTM[9743]="*Atha kho āyasmā bhaddiyo teneva antaravassena tisso vijjā sacchākāsi.**During that very rainy season Venerable Bhaddiya realized the three insights,*";
P_HTM[9744]="*Āyasmā anuruddho dibbacakkhuṃ uppādesi.**Venerable Anuruddha obtained clairvoyance,*";
P_HTM[9745]="*Āyasmā ānando sotāpattiphalaṃ sacchākāsi.**Venerable Ānanda realized stream-entry,*";
P_HTM[9746]="*Devadatto pothujjanikaṃ iddhiṃ abhinipphādesi.**whereas Devadatta obtained supernormal powers, but no stage of awakening.*";
P_HTM[9747]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā bhaddiyo araññagatopi rukkhamūlagatopi suññāgāragatopi abhikkhaṇaṃ udānaṃ udānesi—**When Bhaddiya was in the wilderness, at the foot of a tree, or in an empty dwelling, he frequently uttered a heartfelt exclamation:*";
P_HTM[9748]="*“aho sukhaṃ, aho sukhan”ti.**“Oh, what happiness! Oh, what happiness!”*";
P_HTM[9749]="*Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu.**A number of monks went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[9750]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ—**and told him what was happening,*";
P_HTM[9751]="*“āyasmā, bhante, bhaddiyo araññagatopi rukkhamūlagatopi suññāgāragatopi abhikkhaṇaṃ udānaṃ udānesi—* **";
P_HTM[9752]="*‘aho sukhaṃ, aho sukhan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[9753]="*Nissaṃsayaṃ kho, bhante, āyasmā bhaddiyo anabhiratova brahmacariyaṃ carati.**adding, “No doubt Bhaddiya is dissatisfied with the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[9754]="*Taṃyeva vā purimaṃ rajjasukhaṃ samanussaranto araññagatopi rukkhamūlagatopi suññāgāragatopi abhikkhaṇaṃ udānaṃ udānesi—**It’s because he’s recalling his former happiness as a king that he is saying this.”*";
P_HTM[9755]="*‘aho sukhaṃ, aho sukhan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[9756]="*Atha kho bhagavā aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ āmantesi—**The Buddha addressed a certain monk:*";
P_HTM[9757]="*“ehi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, mama vacanena bhaddiyaṃ bhikkhuṃ āmantehi—**“Go, monk, and in my name say to Bhaddiya,*";
P_HTM[9758]="*‘satthā taṃ, āvuso bhaddiya, āmantetī’”ti.**‘Bhaddiya, the Teacher is calling you.’”*";
P_HTM[9759]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu bhagavato paṭissutvā yenāyasmā bhaddiyo tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ bhaddiyaṃ etadavoca—**Saying, “Yes, Sir,” he did just that.*";
P_HTM[9760]="*“satthā taṃ, āvuso bhaddiya, āmantetī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[9761]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā bhaddiyo tassa bhikkhuno paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Bhaddiya consented. He then went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down.*";
P_HTM[9762]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ bhaddiyaṃ bhagavā etadavoca—**And the Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[9763]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, bhaddiya, araññagatopi rukkhamūlagatopi suññāgāragatopi abhikkhaṇaṃ udānaṃ udānesi—**“Is it true, Bhaddiya, that when you’re in the wilderness, at the foot of a tree, or in an empty dwelling, you frequently utter a heartfelt exclamation:*";
P_HTM[9764]="*‘aho sukhaṃ, aho sukhan’”ti?**‘Oh, what happiness! Oh, what happiness!’?”*";
P_HTM[9765]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti.**“Yes, Venerable Sir.”*";
P_HTM[9766]="*“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, bhaddiya, atthavasaṃ sampassamāno araññagatopi rukkhamūlagatopi suññāgāragatopi abhikkhaṇaṃ udānaṃ udānesi—**“But why do you say this?”*";
P_HTM[9767]="*‘aho sukhaṃ, aho sukhan’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[9768]="*“Pubbe me, bhante, rañño satopi antopi antepure rakkhā susaṃvihitā hoti, bahipi antepure rakkhā susaṃvihitā hoti, antopi nagare rakkhā susaṃvihitā hoti, bahipi nagare rakkhā susaṃvihitā hoti, antopi janapade rakkhā susaṃvihitā hoti, bahipi janapade rakkhā susaṃvihitā hoti.**“In the past, when I was a king, I was well protected within and outside the royal compound, within and outside of town, and within and outside of the country.*";
P_HTM[9769]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhante, evaṃ rakkhitopi gopitopi santo bhīto ubbiggo ussaṅkī utrasto viharāmi.**But although I was protected and guarded in this way, I was fearful, agitated, and distrustful.*";
P_HTM[9770]="*Etarahi kho pana ahaṃ eko, bhante, araññagatopi rukkhamūlagatopi suññāgāragatopi abhīto anubbiggo anussaṅkī anutrasto appossukko pannalomo paradattavutto migabhūtena cetasā viharāmīti.**But now, Sir, when I’m in the wilderness, at the foot of a tree, or in an empty dwelling, I’m free from fear, agitation, and distrust. I’m free from bother, relaxed, living on what’s given by others, with a mind as free as a wild animal.*";
P_HTM[9771]="*Imaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, atthavasaṃ sampassamāno araññagatopi rukkhamūlagatopi suññāgāragatopi abhikkhaṇaṃ udānaṃ udānemi—**This is why I say this.”*";
P_HTM[9772]="*‘aho sukhaṃ, aho sukhan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[9773]="*Atha kho bhagavā etamatthaṃ viditvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ udānaṃ udānesi—**Seeing the significance of this, on that occasion the Buddha uttered a heartfelt exclamation:*";
P_HTM[9774]="*“Yassantarato na santi kopā,**“They who have no anger within,*";
P_HTM[9775]="*Iti bhavābhavatañca vītivatto;**Gone beyond any kind of existence,*";
P_HTM[9776]="*Taṃ vigatabhayaṃ sukhiṃ asokaṃ,**Happy, free from fear and sorrow—*";
P_HTM[9777]="*Devā nānubhavanti dassanāyā”ti.**Even the gods are unable to see them.”*";
P_HTM[9778]="*2. Devadattavatthu**1.2 The account of Devadatta*";
P_HTM[9779]="*Atha kho bhagavā anupiyāyaṃ yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena kosambī tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**When the Buddha had stayed at Anupiyā for as long as he liked, he set out wandering toward Kosambī.*";
P_HTM[9780]="*Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena kosambī tadavasari.**When he eventually arrived,*";
P_HTM[9781]="*Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme.**he stayed in Ghosita’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[9782]="*Atha kho devadattassa rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi—**At this time, while in seclusion, Devadatta thought,*";
P_HTM[9783]="*“kaṃ nu kho ahaṃ pasādeyyaṃ, yasmiṃ me pasanne bahulābhasakkāro uppajjeyyā”ti?**“Who might I inspire to have confidence in me, so that I’d get much gain and honor?”*";
P_HTM[9784]="*Atha kho devadattassa etadahosi—**And it occurred to him,*";
P_HTM[9785]="*“ayaṃ kho ajātasattu kumāro taruṇo ceva āyatiṃ bhaddo ca.**“Prince Ajātasattu is young and has a bright future.*";
P_HTM[9786]="*Yannūnāhaṃ ajātasattuṃ kumāraṃ pasādeyyaṃ.**Why don’t I inspire him to have confidence in me?*";
P_HTM[9787]="*Tasmiṃ me pasanne bahulābhasakkāro uppajjissatī”ti.**I’ll then get much gain and honor.”*";
P_HTM[9788]="*Atha kho devadatto senāsanaṃ saṃsāmetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena rājagahaṃ tena pakkāmi.**Devadatta put his dwelling in order, took his bowl and robes, and left for Rājagaha,*";
P_HTM[9789]="*Anupubbena yena rājagahaṃ tadavasari.**where he eventually arrived.*";
P_HTM[9790]="*Atha kho devadatto sakavaṇṇaṃ paṭisaṃharitvā kumārakavaṇṇaṃ abhinimminitvā ahimekhalikāya ajātasattussa kumārassa ucchaṅge pāturahosi.**He then transformed himself into a boy wearing a snake as a belt and appeared on Prince Ajātasattu’s lap.*";
P_HTM[9791]="*Atha kho ajātasattu kumāro bhīto ahosi, ubbiggo ussaṅkī utrasto.**When Ajātasattu became fearful and agitated,*";
P_HTM[9792]="*Atha kho devadatto ajātasattuṃ kumāraṃ etadavoca—**Devadatta said to him,*";
P_HTM[9793]="*“bhāyasi maṃ tvaṃ, kumārā”ti?**“Are you afraid of me, Prince?”*";
P_HTM[9794]="*“Āma bhāyāmi.**“I am.*";
P_HTM[9795]="*Kosi tvan”ti?**Who are you?”*";
P_HTM[9796]="*“Ahaṃ devadatto”ti.**“I’m Devadatta.”*";
P_HTM[9797]="*“Sace kho tvaṃ, bhante, ayyo devadatto, iṅgha sakeneva vaṇṇena pātubhavassū”ti.**“If you are Venerable Devadatta, then please appear in your own form.”*";
P_HTM[9798]="*Atha kho devadatto kumārakavaṇṇaṃ paṭisaṃharitvā saṅghāṭipattacīvaradharo ajātasattussa kumārassa purato aṭṭhāsi.**Devadatta abandoned the form of a boy and then stood in front of Ajātasattu, wearing his robes and carrying his bowl.*";
P_HTM[9799]="*Atha kho ajātasattu kumāro devadattassa iminā iddhipāṭihāriyena abhippasanno pañcahi rathasatehi sāyaṃ pātaṃ upaṭṭhānaṃ gacchati, pañca ca thālipākasatāni bhattābhihāro abhiharīyati.**By means of this wonder Devadatta was able to inspire Ajātasattu to have confidence in him. Ajātasattu then attended on him morning and evening, with five hundred carriages and a meal offering of five hundred dishes of food.*";
P_HTM[9800]="*Atha kho devadattassa lābhasakkārasilokena abhibhūtassa pariyādinnacittassa evarūpaṃ icchāgataṃ uppajji—**Overcome by gain, honor, and fame,*";
P_HTM[9801]="*“ahaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ pariharissāmī”ti.**Devadatta started desiring to lead the Sangha of monks.*";
P_HTM[9802]="*Saha cittuppādāva devadatto tassā iddhiyā parihāyi.**But with the appearance of that thought, his supernormal powers disappeared.*";
P_HTM[9803]="*Tena kho pana samayena kakudho nāma koḷiyaputto, āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa upaṭṭhāko, adhunā kālaṅkato aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno.**At that time Kakudha the Koḷiyan, the attendant to Venerable Mahāmoggallāna, had recently died and been reborn in a mind-made body.*";
P_HTM[9804]="*Tassa evarūpo attabhāvappaṭilābho hoti—**He had acquired a body*";
P_HTM[9805]="*seyyathāpi nāma dve vā tīṇi vā māgadhakāni gāmakkhettāni.**two or three times the size of the fields of a Magadhan village.*";
P_HTM[9806]="*So tena attabhāvappaṭilābhena neva attānaṃ na paraṃ byābādheti.**Yet he harmed neither himself nor others with that body.*";
P_HTM[9807]="*Atha kho kakudho devaputto yenāyasmā mahāmoggallāno tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi.**Soon afterwards the god Kakudha approached Mahāmoggallāna, bowed down,*";
P_HTM[9808]="*Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho kakudho devaputto āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ etadavoca—**and told him*";
P_HTM[9809]="*“devadattassa, bhante, lābhasakkārasilokena abhibhūtassa pariyādinnacittassa evarūpaṃ icchāgataṃ uppajji—**about Devadatta’s desire*";
P_HTM[9810]="*‘ahaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ pariharissāmī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[9811]="*Saha cittuppādāva, bhante, devadatto tassā iddhiyā parihīno”ti.**and the disappearance of his supernormal powers.*";
P_HTM[9812]="*Idamavoca kakudho devaputto.* **";
P_HTM[9813]="*Idaṃ vatvā āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tattheva antaradhāyi.**He then bowed down, circumambulated Mahāmoggallāna with his right side toward him, and disappeared on the spot.*";
P_HTM[9814]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Mahāmoggallāna then went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[9815]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and told him all that had happened.*";
P_HTM[9816]="*“kakudho nāma, bhante, koḷiyaputto mama upaṭṭhāko adhunā kālaṅkato aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno.* **";
P_HTM[9817]="*Tassa evarūpo attabhāvappaṭilābho—* **";
P_HTM[9818]="*seyyathāpi nāma dve vā tīṇi vā māgadhakāni gāmakkhettāni.* **";
P_HTM[9819]="*So tena attabhāvappaṭilābhena neva attānaṃ na paraṃ byābādheti.* **";
P_HTM[9820]="*Atha kho, bhante, kakudho devaputto yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi.* **";
P_HTM[9821]="*Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho, bhante, kakudho devaputto maṃ etadavoca—* **";
P_HTM[9822]="*‘devadattassa, bhante, lābhasakkārasilokena abhibhūtassa pariyādinnacittassa evarūpaṃ icchāgataṃ uppajji—* **";
P_HTM[9823]="*ahaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ pariharissāmīti.* **";
P_HTM[9824]="*Saha cittuppādāva, bhante, devadatto tassā iddhiyā parihīno’ti.* **";
P_HTM[9825]="*Idamavoca, bhante, kakudho devaputto.* **";
P_HTM[9826]="*Idaṃ vatvā maṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tattheva antaradhāyī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[9827]="*“Kiṃ pana te, moggallāna, kakudho devaputto cetasā ceto paricca vidito?**The Buddha said, “But, Moggallāna, have you read Kakudha’s mind*";
P_HTM[9828]="*Yaṃ kiñci kakudho devaputto bhāsati sabbaṃ taṃ tatheva hoti, no aññathā”ti?**so that you know that all he says is just so and not otherwise?”*";
P_HTM[9829]="*“Cetasā ceto paricca vidito ca me, bhante, kakudho devaputto.**“I have, Venerable Sir.”*";
P_HTM[9830]="*Yaṃ kiñci kakudho devaputto bhāsati sabbaṃ taṃ tatheva hoti, no aññathā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[9831]="*“Rakkhassetaṃ, moggallāna, vācaṃ.**“Remember these words, Moggallāna!*";
P_HTM[9832]="*Rakkhassetaṃ, moggallāna, vācaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9833]="*Idāni so moghapuriso attanāva attānaṃ pātukarissati.**Soon that fool will show himself as he truly is.*";
P_HTM[9834]="*3. Pañcasatthukathā**1.3 Discussion of the five kinds of teachers*";
P_HTM[9835]="*Pañcime, moggallāna, satthāro santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Moggallāna, there are five kinds of teachers in the world.*";
P_HTM[9836]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[9837]="*Idha, moggallāna, ekacco satthā aparisuddhasīlo samāno ‘parisuddhasīlomhī’ti paṭijānāti ‘parisuddhaṃ me sīlaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhan’ti ca.**One kind of teacher is impure in behavior, while claiming it is pure.*";
P_HTM[9838]="*Tamenaṃ sāvakā evaṃ jānanti—**His disciples know about his impure behavior,*";
P_HTM[9839]="*‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā aparisuddhasīlo samāno “parisuddhasīlomhī”ti paṭijānāti “parisuddhaṃ me sīlaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhan”ti ca.* **";
P_HTM[9840]="*Mayañceva kho pana gihīnaṃ āroceyyāma, nāssassa manāpaṃ.**but think, ‘It would be unpleasant for him if we inform the householders.*";
P_HTM[9841]="*Yaṃ kho panassa amanāpaṃ, kathaṃ naṃ mayaṃ tena samudācareyyāma?* **";
P_HTM[9842]="*Sammannati kho pana cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena—**Yet it’s because of him that we’re honored with gifts of robes, almsfood, dwellings, and medicines. How then can we inform them?*";
P_HTM[9843]="*yaṃ tumo karissati, tumova tena paññāyissatī’ti.**He will be known through his own actions.’*";
P_HTM[9844]="*Evarūpaṃ kho, moggallāna, satthāraṃ sāvakā sīlato rakkhanti;**The disciples conceal the impure behavior of such a teacher.*";
P_HTM[9845]="*evarūpo ca pana satthā sāvakehi sīlato rakkhaṃ paccāsīsati.**And the teacher expects his disciples to conceal it.*";
P_HTM[9846]="*Puna caparaṃ, moggallāna, idhekacco satthā aparisuddhājīvo samāno ‘parisuddhājīvomhī’ti paṭijānāti ‘parisuddho me ājīvo pariyodāto asaṅkiliṭṭho’ti ca.**Another kind of teacher is impure in livelihood, while claiming it is pure.*";
P_HTM[9847]="*Tamenaṃ sāvakā evaṃ jānanti—**His disciples know about his impure livelihood,*";
P_HTM[9848]="*‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā aparisuddhājīvo samāno “parisuddhājīvomhī”ti paṭijānāti “parisuddho me ājīvo pariyodāto asaṅkiliṭṭho”ti ca.* **";
P_HTM[9849]="*Mayañceva kho pana gihīnaṃ āroceyyāma, nāssassa manāpaṃ.**but think, ‘It would be unpleasant for him if we inform the householders.*";
P_HTM[9850]="*Yaṃ kho panassa amanāpaṃ, kathaṃ naṃ mayaṃ tena samudācareyyāma?* **";
P_HTM[9851]="*Sammannati kho pana cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena—**Yet it’s because of him that we’re honored with gifts of robes, almsfood, dwellings, and medicines. How then can we inform them?*";
P_HTM[9852]="*yaṃ tumo karissati, tumova tena paññāyissatī’ti.**He will be known through his own actions.’*";
P_HTM[9853]="*Evarūpaṃ kho, moggallāna, satthāraṃ sāvakā ājīvato rakkhanti;**The disciples conceal the impure livelihood of such a teacher.*";
P_HTM[9854]="*evarūpo ca pana satthā sāvakehi ājīvato rakkhaṃ paccāsīsati.**And the teacher expects his disciples to conceal it.*";
P_HTM[9855]="*Puna caparaṃ, moggallāna, idhekacco satthā aparisuddhadhammadesano samāno ‘parisuddhadhammadesanomhī’ti paṭijānāti ‘parisuddhā me dhammadesanā pariyodātā asaṅkiliṭṭhā’ti ca.**Still another kind of teacher gives impure teachings, while claiming they are pure.*";
P_HTM[9856]="*Tamenaṃ sāvakā evaṃ jānanti—**His disciples know about his impure teachings,*";
P_HTM[9857]="*‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā aparisuddhadhammadesano samāno “parisuddhadhammadesanomhī”ti paṭijānāti “parisuddhā me dhammadesanā pariyodātā asaṅkiliṭṭhā”ti ca.* **";
P_HTM[9858]="*Mayañceva kho pana gihīnaṃ āroceyyāma, nāssassa manāpaṃ.**but think, ‘It would be unpleasant for him if we inform the householders.*";
P_HTM[9859]="*Yaṃ kho panassa amanāpaṃ, kathaṃ naṃ mayaṃ tena samudācareyyāma?* **";
P_HTM[9860]="*Sammannati kho pana cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena—**Yet it’s because of him that we’re honored with gifts of robes, almsfood, dwellings, and medicines. How then can we inform them?*";
P_HTM[9861]="*yaṃ tumo karissati, tumova tena paññāyissatī’ti.**He will be known through his own actions.’*";
P_HTM[9862]="*Evarūpaṃ kho, moggallāna, satthāraṃ sāvakā dhammadesanato rakkhanti;**The disciples conceal the impure teachings of such a teacher.*";
P_HTM[9863]="*evarūpo ca pana satthā sāvakehi dhammadesanato rakkhaṃ paccāsīsati.**And the teacher expects his disciples to conceal them.*";
P_HTM[9864]="*Puna caparaṃ, moggallāna, idhekacco satthā aparisuddhaveyyākaraṇo samāno ‘parisuddhaveyyākaraṇomhī’ti paṭijānāti ‘parisuddhaṃ me veyyākaraṇaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhan’ti ca.**Still another kind of teacher gives impure explanations, while claiming they are pure.*";
P_HTM[9865]="*Tamenaṃ sāvakā evaṃ jānanti—**His disciples know about his impure explanations,*";
P_HTM[9866]="*‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā aparisuddhaveyyākaraṇo samāno “parisuddhaveyyākaraṇomhī”ti paṭijānāti “parisuddhaṃ me veyyākaraṇaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhan”ti ca.* **";
P_HTM[9867]="*Mayañceva kho pana gihīnaṃ āroceyyāma, nāssassa manāpaṃ.**but think, ‘It would be unpleasant for him if we inform the householders.*";
P_HTM[9868]="*Yaṃ kho panassa amanāpaṃ, kathaṃ naṃ mayaṃ tena samudācareyyāma?* **";
P_HTM[9869]="*Sammannati kho pana cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena—**Yet it’s because of him that we’re honored with gifts of robes, almsfood, dwellings, and medicines. How then can we inform them?*";
P_HTM[9870]="*yaṃ tumo karissati, tumova tena paññāyissatī’ti.**He will be known through his own actions.’*";
P_HTM[9871]="*Evarūpaṃ kho, moggallāna, satthāraṃ sāvakā veyyākaraṇato rakkhanti;**The disciples conceal the impure explanations of such a teacher.*";
P_HTM[9872]="*evarūpo ca pana satthā sāvakehi veyyākaraṇato rakkhaṃ paccāsīsati.**And the teacher expects his disciples to conceal them.*";
P_HTM[9873]="*Puna caparaṃ, moggallāna, idhekacco satthā aparisuddhañāṇadassano samāno ‘parisuddhañāṇadassanomhī’ti paṭijānāti ‘parisuddhaṃ me ñāṇadassanaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhan’ti ca.**Still another kind of teacher has impure knowledge and vision, while claiming they are pure.*";
P_HTM[9874]="*Tamenaṃ sāvakā evaṃ jānanti—**His disciples know about his impure knowledge and vision,*";
P_HTM[9875]="*‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā aparisuddhañāṇadassano samāno “parisuddhañāṇadassanomhī”ti paṭijānāti “parisuddhaṃ me ñāṇadassanaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhan”ti ca.* **";
P_HTM[9876]="*Mayañceva kho pana gihīnaṃ āroceyyāma, nāssassa manāpaṃ.**but think, ‘It would be unpleasant for him if we inform the householders.*";
P_HTM[9877]="*Yaṃ kho panassa amanāpaṃ, kathaṃ naṃ mayaṃ tena samudācareyyāma?* **";
P_HTM[9878]="*Sammannati kho pana cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena—**Yet it’s because of him that we’re honored with gifts of robes, almsfood, dwellings, and medicines. How then can we inform them?*";
P_HTM[9879]="*yaṃ tumo karissati, tumova tena paññāyissatī’ti.**He will be known through his own actions.’*";
P_HTM[9880]="*Evarūpaṃ kho, moggallāna, satthāraṃ sāvakā ñāṇadassanato rakkhanti;**The disciples conceal the impure knowledge and vision of such a teacher.*";
P_HTM[9881]="*evarūpo ca pana satthā sāvakehi ñāṇadassanato rakkhaṃ paccāsīsatīti.**And the teacher expects his disciples to conceal it.*";
P_HTM[9882]="*Ime kho, moggallāna, pañca satthāro santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9883]="*Ahaṃ kho pana, moggallāna, parisuddhasīlo samāno ‘parisuddhasīlomhī’ti paṭijānāmi ‘parisuddhaṃ me sīlaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhan’ti ca.**But in my case, Moggallāna, I claim my behavior is pure because it is.*";
P_HTM[9884]="*Na ca maṃ sāvakā sīlato rakkhanti;**My disciples don’t conceal my behavior*";
P_HTM[9885]="*na cāhaṃ sāvakehi sīlato rakkhaṃ paccāsīsāmi.**and I don’t expect them to do so.*";
P_HTM[9886]="*Parisuddhājīvo samāno …pe…**I claim my livelihood is pure …*";
P_HTM[9887]="*parisuddhadhammadesano samāno …pe…**I claim my teachings are pure …*";
P_HTM[9888]="*parisuddhaveyyākaraṇo samāno …pe…**I claim my explanations are pure …*";
P_HTM[9889]="*parisuddhañāṇadassano samāno ‘parisuddhañāṇadassanomhī’ti paṭijānāmi ‘parisuddhaṃ me ñāṇadassanaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhan’ti ca.**I claim my knowledge and vision are pure because they are.*";
P_HTM[9890]="*Na ca maṃ sāvakā ñāṇadassanato rakkhanti;**My disciples don’t conceal my knowledge and vision*";
P_HTM[9891]="*na cāhaṃ sāvakehi ñāṇadassanato rakkhaṃ paccāsīsāmī”ti.**and I don’t expect them to do so.”*";
P_HTM[9892]="*Atha kho bhagavā kosambiyaṃ yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena rājagahaṃ tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**When the Buddha had stayed at Kosambī for as long as he liked, he set out wandering toward Rājagaha.*";
P_HTM[9893]="*Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena rājagahaṃ tadavasari.**When he eventually arrived,*";
P_HTM[9894]="*Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**he stayed in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[9895]="*Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu.**Then a number of monks went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[9896]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ—**and said,*";
P_HTM[9897]="*“devadattassa, bhante, ajātasattu kumāro pañcahi rathasatehi sāyaṃ pātaṃ upaṭṭhānaṃ gacchati;**“Venerable Sir, Prince Ajātasattu attends on Devadatta morning and evening, with five hundred carriages*";
P_HTM[9898]="*pañca ca thālipākasatāni bhattābhihāro abhiharīyatī”ti.**and a meal offering of five hundred dishes of food.”*";
P_HTM[9899]="*“Mā, bhikkhave, devadattassa lābhasakkārasilokaṃ pihayittha.**“Don’t envy Devadatta, monks, his gain, honor, and fame.*";
P_HTM[9900]="*Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, devadattassa ajātasattu kumāro pañcahi rathasatehi sāyaṃ pātaṃ upaṭṭhānaṃ gamissati, pañca ca thālipākasatāni bhattābhihāro abhiharīyissati, hāniyeva, bhikkhave, devadattassa pāṭikaṅkhā kusalesu dhammesu, no vuḍḍhi.**So long as Prince Ajātasattu treats him like this, Devadatta can be expected to decline in good qualities.*";
P_HTM[9901]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, caṇḍassa kukkurassa nāsāya pittaṃ bhindeyyuṃ, evañhi so, bhikkhave, kukkuro bhiyyoso mattāya caṇḍataro assa;**Just as a fierce dog would get even more fierce if you break a gall bladder on its nose,*";
P_HTM[9902]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, yāvakīvañca devadattassa ajātasattu kumāro pañcahi rathasatehi sāyaṃ pātaṃ upaṭṭhānaṃ gamissati, pañca ca thālipākasatāni bhattābhihāro abhiharīyissati, hāniyeva, bhikkhave, devadattassa pāṭikaṅkhā kusalesu dhammesu, no vuḍḍhi.**so too, so long as Prince Ajātasattu treats like this, Devadatta can be expected to decline in good qualities.*";
P_HTM[9903]="*Attavadhāya, bhikkhave, devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi.**Devadatta’s gain, honor, and fame will cause his destruction and ruin.*";
P_HTM[9904]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, kadalī attavadhāya phalaṃ deti, parābhavāya phalaṃ deti;**Just as a plantain banana tree produces fruit for its own destruction and ruin,*";
P_HTM[9905]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi.**so too do Devadatta’s gain, honor, and fame cause his own destruction and ruin.*";
P_HTM[9906]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, veḷu attavadhāya phalaṃ deti, parābhavāya phalaṃ deti;**Just as a bamboo produces fruit for its own destruction and ruin,*";
P_HTM[9907]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi.**so too do Devadatta’s gain, honor, and fame cause his own destruction and ruin.*";
P_HTM[9908]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, naḷo attavadhāya phalaṃ deti, parābhavāya phalaṃ deti;**Just as a _naḷa_ reed produces fruit for its own destruction and ruin,*";
P_HTM[9909]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi.**so too do Devadatta’s gain, honor, and fame cause his own destruction and ruin.*";
P_HTM[9910]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, assatarī attavadhāya gabbhaṃ gaṇhāti, parābhavāya gabbhaṃ gaṇhāti;**Just as a mule becomes pregnant for its own destruction and ruin,*";
P_HTM[9911]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādīti.**so too do Devadatta’s gain, honor, and fame cause his own destruction and ruin.”*";
P_HTM[9912]="*Phalaṃ ve kadaliṃ hanti,**“The fruit destroys the plantain,*";
P_HTM[9913]="*phalaṃ veḷuṃ phalaṃ naḷaṃ;**And the bamboo and the reed.*";
P_HTM[9914]="*Sakkāro kāpurisaṃ hanti,**Honor destroys the bad person,*";
P_HTM[9915]="*gabbho assatariṃ yathā”ti.**As the fetus destroys the mule.”*";
P_HTM[9916]="*Paṭhamabhāṇavāro niṭṭhito.**The first section for recitation is finished.*";
P_HTM[9917]="*1. Pakāsanīyakamma**2.1 The legal procedure of announcement*";
P_HTM[9918]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā mahatiyā parisāya parivuto dhammaṃ desento nisinno hoti sarājikāya parisāya.**Soon afterwards the Buddha was seated giving a teaching surrounded by a large gathering of people, including the King.*";
P_HTM[9919]="*Atha kho devadatto uṭṭhāyāsanā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**Then Devadatta got up from his seat, put his upper robe over one shoulder, raised his joined palms, and said,*";
P_HTM[9920]="*“jiṇṇo dāni, bhante, bhagavā vuḍḍho mahallako addhagato vayoanuppatto.**“Venerable Sir, you’re now old and close to the end of your life.*";
P_HTM[9921]="*Appossukko dāni, bhante, bhagavā diṭṭhadhammasukhavihāraṃ anuyutto viharatu, mamaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ nissajjatu.**You should live free from bother and enjoy the happiness of the present life. Hand the Sangha of monks over to me.*";
P_HTM[9922]="*Ahaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ pariharissāmī”ti.**Let me lead the Sangha.”*";
P_HTM[9923]="*“Alaṃ, devadatta, mā te rucci bhikkhusaṅghaṃ pariharitun”ti.**“Let it be, Devadatta, don’t think of leading the Sangha of monks.”*";
P_HTM[9924]="*Dutiyampi kho devadatto …pe…**A second time Devadatta said the same thing and got the same reply.*";
P_HTM[9925]="*tatiyampi kho devadatto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**He then said it a third time,*";
P_HTM[9926]="*“jiṇṇo dāni, bhante, bhagavā vuḍḍho mahallako addhagato vayoanuppatto.* **";
P_HTM[9927]="*Appossukko dāni, bhante, bhagavā diṭṭhadhammasukhavihāraṃ anuyutto viharatu, mamaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ nissajjatu.* **";
P_HTM[9928]="*Ahaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ pariharissāmī”ti.**and the Buddha replied:*";
P_HTM[9929]="*“Sāriputtamoggallānānampi kho ahaṃ, devadatta, bhikkhusaṅghaṃ na nissajjeyyaṃ, kiṃ pana tuyhaṃ chavassa kheḷāsakassā”ti.**“I wouldn’t even hand the Sangha over to Sāriputta and Mogallāna, so why then to you, a wretched devourer of junk?”*";
P_HTM[9930]="*Atha kho devadatto—**Devadatta thought,*";
P_HTM[9931]="*sarājikāya maṃ bhagavā parisāya kheḷāsakavādena apasādeti, sāriputtamoggallāneva ukkaṃsatīti—**“The Buddha disparages me in front of a gathering that includes the king as a devourer of junk, while praising Sāriputta and Mogallāna,”*";
P_HTM[9932]="*kupito anattamano bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**and he bowed down in anger, circumambulated the Buddha with his right side toward him, and left.*";
P_HTM[9933]="*Ayañcarahi devadattassa bhagavati paṭhamo āghāto ahosi.**This was the first time Devadatta had ill will toward the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[9934]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[9935]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho devadattassa rājagahe pakāsanīyaṃ kammaṃ karotu—**“Well then, the Sangha should do a legal procedure to announce the following about Devadatta in Rājagaha:*";
P_HTM[9936]="*‘pubbe devadattassa aññā pakati ahosi, idāni aññā pakati.**‘Previously Devadatta had one nature, now he has another.*";
P_HTM[9937]="*Yaṃ devadatto kareyya kāyena vācāya, na tena buddho vā dhammo vā saṅgho vā daṭṭhabbo, devadattova tena daṭṭhabbo’ti.**Whatever Devadatta does by body or speech has nothing to do with the Buddha, the Teaching, or the Sangha, but only with Devadatta.’*";
P_HTM[9938]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, kātabbaṃ.**And it should be done like this.*";
P_HTM[9939]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[9940]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[9941]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ saṅgho devadattassa rājagahe pakāsanīyaṃ kammaṃ kareyya—**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should do a legal procedure to announce the following about Devadatta in Rājagaha:*";
P_HTM[9942]="*“pubbe devadattassa aññā pakati ahosi, idāni aññā pakati.**‘Previously Devadatta had one nature, now he has another.*";
P_HTM[9943]="*Yaṃ devadatto kareyya kāyena vācāya, na tena buddho vā dhammo vā saṅgho vā daṭṭhabbo, devadattova tena daṭṭhabbo”ti.**Whatever Devadatta does by body or speech has nothing to do with the Buddha, the Teaching, or the Sangha, but only with Devadatta.’*";
P_HTM[9944]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[9945]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[9946]="*Saṅgho devadattassa rājagahe pakāsanīyaṃ kammaṃ karoti—**The Sangha does a legal procedure to announce the following about Devadatta in Rājagaha:*";
P_HTM[9947]="*“pubbe devadattassa aññā pakati ahosi, idāni aññā pakati.**‘Previously Devadatta had one nature, now he has another.*";
P_HTM[9948]="*Yaṃ devadatto kareyya kāyena vācāya, na tena buddho vā dhammo vā saṅgho vā daṭṭhabbo, devadattova tena daṭṭhabbo”ti.**Whatever Devadatta does by body or speech has nothing to do with the Buddha, the Teaching, or the Sangha, but only with Devadatta.’*";
P_HTM[9949]="*Yassāyasmato khamati devadattassa rājagahe pakāsanīyassa kammassa karaṇaṃ—**Any monk who approves of doing this procedure*";
P_HTM[9950]="*“pubbe devadattassa aññā pakati ahosi, idāni aññā pakati, yaṃ devadatto kareyya kāyena vācāya, na tena buddho vā dhammo vā saṅgho vā daṭṭhabbo, devadattova tena daṭṭhabbo”ti—* **";
P_HTM[9951]="*so tuṇhassa;**should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[9952]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[9953]="*Kataṃ saṅghena devadattassa rājagahe pakāsanīyaṃ kammaṃ—**The Sangha has done a legal procedure to announce the following about Devadatta in Rājagaha:*";
P_HTM[9954]="*“pubbe devadattassa aññā pakati ahosi, idāni aññā pakati.**‘Previously Devadatta had one nature, now he has another.*";
P_HTM[9955]="*Yaṃ devadatto kareyya kāyena vācāya, na tena buddho vā dhammo vā saṅgho vā daṭṭhabbo, devadattova tena daṭṭhabbo”ti.**Whatever Devadatta does by body or speech has nothing to do with the Buddha, the Teaching, or the Sangha, but only with Devadatta.’*";
P_HTM[9956]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I’ll remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[9957]="*Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ āmantesi—**And the Buddha addressed Sāriputta:*";
P_HTM[9958]="*“tena hi tvaṃ, sāriputta, devadattaṃ rājagahe pakāsehī”ti.**“Well then, Sāriputta, make the announcement about Devadatta in Rājagaha.”*";
P_HTM[9959]="*“Pubbe mayā, bhante, devadattassa rājagahe vaṇṇo bhāsito—**“Previously, Venerable Sir, I have praised Devadatta in Rājagaha,*";
P_HTM[9960]="*‘mahiddhiko godhiputto, mahānubhāvo godhiputto’ti.**saying, ‘The Godhian is powerful and mighty.’*";
P_HTM[9961]="*Kathāhaṃ, bhante, devadattaṃ rājagahe pakāsemī”ti?**How then can I now make this announcement about Devadatta in Rājagaha?”*";
P_HTM[9962]="*“Nanu tayā, sāriputta, bhūtoyeva devadattassa rājagahe vaṇṇo bhāsito—**“Didn’t you truthfully praise Devadatta in Rājagaha*";
P_HTM[9963]="*‘mahiddhiko godhiputto, mahānubhāvo godhiputto’”ti?**when you said that?”*";
P_HTM[9964]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti.**“Yes.”*";
P_HTM[9965]="*“Evameva kho tvaṃ, sāriputta, bhūtaṃyeva devadattaṃ rājagahe pakāsehī”ti.**“In the same way, you should truthfully make an announcement about Devadatta in Rājagaha.”*";
P_HTM[9966]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā sāriputto bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes.”*";
P_HTM[9967]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi—**And the Buddha addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[9968]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho sāriputtaṃ sammannatu devadattaṃ rājagahe pakāsetuṃ—**“Well then, the Sangha should appoint Sāriputta to make that announcement about Devadatta in Rājagaha.*";
P_HTM[9969]="*‘pubbe devadattassa aññā pakati ahosi, idāni aññā pakati.* **";
P_HTM[9970]="*Yaṃ devadatto kareyya kāyena vācāya, na tena buddho vā dhammo vā saṅgho vā daṭṭhabbo, devadattova tena daṭṭhabbo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[9971]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sammannitabbo.**And he should be appointed like this.*";
P_HTM[9972]="*Paṭhamaṃ sāriputto yācitabbo.**First Sāriputta should be asked,*";
P_HTM[9973]="*Yācitvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**and then a competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[9974]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[9975]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ sammanneyya devadattaṃ rājagahe pakāsetuṃ—**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should appoint Venerable Sāriputta to make the following announcement about Devadatta in Rājagaha:*";
P_HTM[9976]="*“pubbe devadattassa aññā pakati ahosi, idāni aññā pakati.**‘Previously Devadatta had one nature, now he has another.*";
P_HTM[9977]="*Yaṃ devadatto kareyya kāyena vācāya, na tena buddho vā dhammo vā saṅgho vā daṭṭhabbo, devadattova tena daṭṭhabbo”ti.**Whatever Devadatta does by body or speech has nothing to do with the Buddha, the Teaching, or the Sangha, but only with Devadatta.’*";
P_HTM[9978]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[9979]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[9980]="*Saṅgho āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ sammannati devadattaṃ rājagahe pakāsetuṃ—**The Sangha appoints Venerable Sāriputta to make the following announcement about Devadatta in Rājagaha:*";
P_HTM[9981]="*“pubbe devadattassa aññā pakati ahosi, idāni aññā pakati, yaṃ devadatto kareyya kāyena vācāya, na tena buddho vā dhammo vā saṅgho vā daṭṭhabbo, devadattova tena daṭṭhabbo”ti.**‘Previously Devadatta had one nature, now he has another. Whatever Devadatta does by body or speech has nothing to do with the Buddha, the Teaching, or the Sangha, but only with Devadatta.’*";
P_HTM[9982]="*Yassāyasmato khamati, āyasmato sāriputtassa sammuti devadattaṃ rājagahe pakāsetuṃ—**Any monk who approves of appointing Venerable Sāriputta to make this announcement*";
P_HTM[9983]="*“pubbe devadattassa aññā pakati ahosi, idāni aññā pakati, yaṃ devadatto kareyya kāyena vācāya, na tena buddho vā dhammo vā saṅgho vā daṭṭhabbo, devadattova tena daṭṭhabbo”ti—* **";
P_HTM[9984]="*so tuṇhassa;**should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[9985]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[9986]="*Sammato saṅghena āyasmā sāriputto devadattaṃ rājagahe pakāsetuṃ—**The Sangha has appointed Venerable Sāriputta to make the following announcement about Devadatta in Rājagaha:*";
P_HTM[9987]="*“pubbe devadattassa aññā pakati ahosi, idāni aññā pakati.**‘Previously Devadatta had one nature, now he has another.*";
P_HTM[9988]="*Yaṃ devadatto kareyya kāyena vācāya, na tena buddho vā dhammo vā saṅgho vā daṭṭhabbo, devadattova tena daṭṭhabbo”ti.**Whatever Devadatta does by body or speech has nothing to do with the Buddha, the Teaching, or the Sangha, but only with Devadatta.’*";
P_HTM[9989]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I’ll remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[9990]="*Sammato ca āyasmā sāriputto sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ rājagahaṃ pavisitvā devadattaṃ rājagahe pakāsesi—**When he had been appointed, Sāriputta entered Rājagaha accompanied by a number of monks. He then made that announcement about Devadatta:*";
P_HTM[9991]="*“pubbe devadattassa aññā pakati ahosi, idāni aññā pakati.**“Previously Devadatta had one nature, now he has another.*";
P_HTM[9992]="*Yaṃ devadatto kareyya kāyena vācāya, na tena buddho vā dhammo vā saṅgho vā daṭṭhabbo, devadattova tena daṭṭhabbo”ti.**Whatever Devadatta does by body or speech has nothing to do with the Buddha, the Teaching, or the Sangha, but only with Devadatta.”*";
P_HTM[9993]="*Tattha ye te manussā assaddhā appasannā dubbuddhino, te evamāhaṃsu—**The foolish people there, those with little faith and confidence, said,*";
P_HTM[9994]="*“usūyakā ime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā devadattassa lābhasakkāraṃ usūyantī”ti.**“These Sakyan monastics are envious of Devadatta’s gain and honor.”*";
P_HTM[9995]="*Ye pana te manussā saddhā pasannā paṇḍitā byattā buddhimanto, te evamāhaṃsu—**But the wise ones, those with faith and confidence, said,*";
P_HTM[9996]="*“na kho idaṃ orakaṃ bhavissati yathā bhagavā devadattaṃ rājagahe pakāsāpetī”ti.**“This must be a serious matter, seeing as the Buddha has an announcement made about Devadatta in Rājagaha.”*";
P_HTM[9997]="*2. Ajātasattukumāravatthu**2.2 The account of Prince Ajātasattu*";
P_HTM[9998]="*Atha kho devadatto yena ajātasattu kumāro tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā ajātasattuṃ kumāraṃ etadavoca—**Soon afterwards Devadatta went to Prince Ajātasattu and said,*";
P_HTM[9999]="*“pubbe kho, kumāra, manussā dīghāyukā, etarahi appāyukā.**“Formerly, Prince, people were long-lived, but now they are short-lived.*";
P_HTM[10000]="*Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati yaṃ tvaṃ kumārova samāno kālaṃ kareyyāsi.**It’s possible that you might die while still a prince.*";
P_HTM[10001]="*Tena hi tvaṃ, kumāra, pitaraṃ hantvā rājā hohi.**So kill your father and become the King.*";
P_HTM[10002]="*Ahaṃ bhagavantaṃ hantvā buddho bhavissāmī”ti.**And I’ll kill the Buddha and become the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[10003]="*Atha kho ajātasattu kumāro—**Ajātasattu thought,*";
P_HTM[10004]="*“ayyo kho devadatto mahiddhiko mahānubhāvo, jāneyyāsi ayyo devadatto”ti—**“Venerable Devadatta is powerful and mighty. He would know.”*";
P_HTM[10005]="*ūruyā potthanikaṃ bandhitvā divā divassa bhīto ubbiggo ussaṅkī utrasto sahasā antepuraṃ pāvisi.**So he bound a dagger to his thigh and, fearful and agitated, he hastily entered the royal compound in the middle of the day.*";
P_HTM[10006]="*Addasāsuṃ kho antepure upacārakā mahāmattā ajātasattuṃ kumāraṃ divā divassa bhītaṃ ubbiggaṃ ussaṅkiṃ utrastaṃ sahasā antepuraṃ pavisantaṃ;**The officials in the royal compound saw Ajātasattu’s strange behavior*";
P_HTM[10007]="*disvāna aggahesuṃ.**and seized him.*";
P_HTM[10008]="*Te vicinantā ūruyā potthanikaṃ baddhaṃ disvāna ajātasattuṃ kumāraṃ etadavocuṃ—**When they examined him, they found the dagger tied to his thigh. They asked him*";
P_HTM[10009]="*“kiṃ tvaṃ, kumāra, kattukāmosī”ti?**what he was up to.*";
P_HTM[10010]="*“Pitaramhi hantukāmo”ti.**“I want to kill my father.”*";
P_HTM[10011]="*“Kenāsi ussāhito”ti?**“Who has instigated you?”*";
P_HTM[10012]="*“Ayyena devadattenā”ti.**“Venerable Devadatta.”*";
P_HTM[10013]="*Ekacce mahāmattā evaṃ matiṃ akaṃsu—**Some officials opined,*";
P_HTM[10014]="*“kumāro ca hantabbo, devadatto ca, sabbe ca bhikkhū hantabbā”ti.**“The Prince should be executed, as well as Devadatta and all the monks.”*";
P_HTM[10015]="*Ekacce mahāmattā evaṃ matiṃ akaṃsu—**Others opined,*";
P_HTM[10016]="*“na bhikkhū hantabbā.**“The monks should not be executed;*";
P_HTM[10017]="*Na bhikkhū kiñci aparajjhanti.**they haven’t done anything wrong.*";
P_HTM[10018]="*Kumāro ca hantabbo, devadatto cā”ti.**The Prince should be executed, as well as Devadatta.”*";
P_HTM[10019]="*Ekacce mahāmattā evaṃ matiṃ akaṃsu—**Others again opined,*";
P_HTM[10020]="*“na kumāro ca hantabbo, na devadatto.**“Neither the Prince nor Devadatta*";
P_HTM[10021]="*Na bhikkhū hantabbā.**nor the monks should be executed.*";
P_HTM[10022]="*Rañño ārocetabbaṃ.**The King should be informed,*";
P_HTM[10023]="*Yathā rājā vakkhati tathā karissāmā”ti.**and we should do as he says.”*";
P_HTM[10024]="*Atha kho te mahāmattā ajātasattuṃ kumāraṃ ādāya yena rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro tenupasaṅkamiṃsu, upasaṅkamitvā rañño māgadhassa seniyassa bimbisārassa etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**Taking Ajātasattu with them, they went to King Seniya Bimbisāra of Magadha and informed him of what had happened.*";
P_HTM[10025]="*“Kathaṃ, bhaṇe, mahāmattehi mati katā”ti?**The King said, “What do you all think?”*";
P_HTM[10026]="*“Ekacce, deva, mahāmattā evaṃ matiṃ akaṃsu—**And they told him their views.*";
P_HTM[10027]="*‘kumāro ca hantabbo, devadatto ca, sabbe ca bhikkhū hantabbā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[10028]="*Ekacce mahāmattā evaṃ matiṃ akaṃsu—* **";
P_HTM[10029]="*‘na bhikkhū hantabbā.* **";
P_HTM[10030]="*Na bhikkhū kiñci aparajjhanti.* **";
P_HTM[10031]="*Kumāro ca hantabbo, devadatto cā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[10032]="*Ekacce mahāmattā evaṃ matiṃ akaṃsu—* **";
P_HTM[10033]="*‘na kumāro ca hantabbo, na devadatto.* **";
P_HTM[10034]="*Na bhikkhū hantabbā.* **";
P_HTM[10035]="*Rañño ārocetabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10036]="*Yathā rājā vakkhati tathā karissāmā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10037]="*“Kiṃ, bhaṇe, karissati buddho vā dhammo vā saṅgho vā?**The King said, “What has this to do with the Buddha, the Teaching, and the Sangha?*";
P_HTM[10038]="*Nanu bhagavatā paṭikacceva devadatto rājagahe pakāsāpito—**Didn’t the Buddha have an announcement made in Rājagaha as a warning:*";
P_HTM[10039]="*‘pubbe devadattassa aññā pakati ahosi, idāni aññā pakati.**‘Previously Devadatta had one nature, now he has another.*";
P_HTM[10040]="*Yaṃ devadatto kareyya kāyena vācāya, na tena buddho vā dhammo vā saṅgho vā daṭṭhabbo, devadattova tena daṭṭhabbo’”ti?**Whatever Devadatta does by body or speech has nothing to do with the Buddha, the Teaching, or the Sangha, but only with Devadatta’?”*";
P_HTM[10041]="*Tattha ye te mahāmattā evaṃ matiṃ akaṃsu—**And he fired those officials who had suggested*";
P_HTM[10042]="*“kumāro ca hantabbo devadatto ca;**to execute the Prince, Devadatta,*";
P_HTM[10043]="*sabbe ca bhikkhū hantabbā”ti;**and the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[10044]="*te aṭṭhāne akāsi.* **";
P_HTM[10045]="*Ye te mahāmattā evaṃ matiṃ akaṃsu—**he demoted those who had suggested*";
P_HTM[10046]="*“na bhikkhū hantabbā;* **";
P_HTM[10047]="*na bhikkhū kiñci aparajjhanti;* **";
P_HTM[10048]="*kumāro ca hantabbo devadatto cā”ti;**to execute the Prince and Devadatta;*";
P_HTM[10049]="*te nīce ṭhāne ṭhapesi.* **";
P_HTM[10050]="*Ye te mahāmattā evaṃ matiṃ akaṃsu—**and he promoted those who had suggested*";
P_HTM[10051]="*“na kumāro ca hantabbo, na devadatto;* **";
P_HTM[10052]="*na bhikkhū hantabbā;* **";
P_HTM[10053]="*rañño ārocetabbaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[10054]="*yathā rājā vakkhati tathā karissāmā”ti;**to act according to the King’s orders.*";
P_HTM[10055]="*te ucce ṭhāne ṭhapesi.* **";
P_HTM[10056]="*Atha kho rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro ajātasattuṃ kumāraṃ etadavoca—**The King then said to Ajātasattu,*";
P_HTM[10057]="*“kissa maṃ tvaṃ, kumāra, hantukāmosī”ti?**“Why do you want to kill me?”*";
P_HTM[10058]="*“Rajjenāmhi, deva, atthiko”ti.**“I want to rule, sir.”*";
P_HTM[10059]="*“Sace kho tvaṃ, kumāra, rajjena atthiko, etaṃ te rajjan”ti ajātasattussa kumārassa rajjaṃ niyyādesi.**“If you want to rule, the kingdom is yours.” And he handed the rulership over to the Prince.*";
P_HTM[10060]="*3. Abhimārapesana**2.3 The sending of assassins*";
P_HTM[10061]="*Atha kho devadatto yena ajātasattu kumāro tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā ajātasattuṃ kumāraṃ etadavoca—**Soon afterwards Devadatta went to Ajātasattu and said,*";
P_HTM[10062]="*“purise, mahārāja, āṇāpehi, ye samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ jīvitā voropessantī”ti.**“Great king, tell your men to kill the ascetic Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[10063]="*Atha kho ajātasattu kumāro manusse āṇāpesi—**And the King told his men,*";
P_HTM[10064]="*“yathā, bhaṇe, ayyo devadatto āha tathā kareyyāthā”ti.**“Do as Venerable Devadatta says.”*";
P_HTM[10065]="*Atha kho devadatto ekaṃ purisaṃ āṇāpesi—**Devadatta then told one man,*";
P_HTM[10066]="*“gacchāvuso, amukasmiṃ okāse samaṇo gotamo viharati.**“Go to such and such a place where the ascetic Gotama is staying.*";
P_HTM[10067]="*Taṃ jīvitā voropetvā iminā maggena āgacchā”ti.**Kill him and return via this path.”*";
P_HTM[10068]="*Tasmiṃ magge dve purise ṭhapesi—**On that path he stationed two men, saying,*";
P_HTM[10069]="*“yo iminā maggena eko puriso āgacchati, taṃ jīvitā voropetvā iminā maggena āgacchathā”ti.**“Kill the man who comes along this path and return via that path.”*";
P_HTM[10070]="*Tasmiṃ magge cattāro purise ṭhapesi—**On that path he stationed four men, saying,*";
P_HTM[10071]="*“ye iminā maggena dve purisā āgacchanti, te jīvitā voropetvā iminā maggena āgacchathā”ti.**“Kill the two men who come along this path and return via that path.”*";
P_HTM[10072]="*Tasmiṃ magge aṭṭha purise ṭhapesi—**On that path he stationed eight men, saying,*";
P_HTM[10073]="*“ye iminā maggena cattāro purisā āgacchanti, te jīvitā voropetvā iminā maggena āgacchathā”ti.**“Kill the four men who come along this path and return via that path.”*";
P_HTM[10074]="*Tasmiṃ magge soḷasa purise ṭhapesi—**On that path he stationed sixteen men, saying,*";
P_HTM[10075]="*“ye iminā maggena aṭṭha purisā āgacchanti, te jīvitā voropetvā āgacchathā”ti.**“Kill the eight men who come along this path and then return.”*";
P_HTM[10076]="*Atha kho so eko puriso asicammaṃ gahetvā dhanukalāpaṃ sannayhitvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato avidūre bhīto ubbiggo ussaṅkī utrasto patthaddhena kāyena aṭṭhāsi.**Soon afterwards that one man took a sword and shield, fastened on a bow and quiver, and went to the Buddha. When he got close, he became fearful and agitated, his body rigid.*";
P_HTM[10077]="*Addasā kho bhagavā taṃ purisaṃ bhītaṃ ubbiggaṃ ussaṅkiṃ utrastaṃ patthaddhena kāyena ṭhitaṃ.**The Buddha saw him*";
P_HTM[10078]="*Disvāna taṃ purisaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[10079]="*“ehāvuso, mā bhāyī”ti.**“Come, don’t be afraid.”*";
P_HTM[10080]="*Atha kho so puriso asicammaṃ ekamantaṃ karitvā dhanukalāpaṃ nikkhipitvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato pādesu sirasā nipatitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**He then placed his sword and shield to one side, put down his bow and quiver, and went up to the Buddha. He bowed down with his head at the Buddha’s feet, and said,*";
P_HTM[10081]="*“accayo maṃ, bhante, accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ, yohaṃ duṭṭhacitto vadhakacitto idhūpasaṅkanto.**“Sir, I’ve made a mistake. I’ve been foolish, confused, and unskillful in coming here with an evil mind intent on murder.*";
P_HTM[10082]="*Tassa me, bhante, bhagavā accayaṃ accayato paṭiggaṇhātu āyatiṃ saṃvarāyā”ti.**Please forgive me so that I may restrain myself in the future.”*";
P_HTM[10083]="*“Taggha tvaṃ, āvuso, accayo accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ, yaṃ tvaṃ duṭṭhacitto vadhakacitto idhūpasaṅkanto.**“You have certainly made a mistake. You’ve been foolish, confused, and unskillful.*";
P_HTM[10084]="*Yato ca kho tvaṃ, āvuso, accayaṃ accayato disvā yathādhammaṃ paṭikarosi, taṃ te mayaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma.**But since you acknowledge your mistake and make proper amends, I forgive you.*";
P_HTM[10085]="*Vuḍḍhi hesā, āvuso, ariyassa vinaye—**For this is called growth in the training of the noble ones:*";
P_HTM[10086]="*yo accayaṃ accayato disvā yathādhammaṃ paṭikaroti, āyatiṃ saṃvaraṃ āpajjatī”ti.**acknowledging a mistake, making proper amends, and undertaking restraint for the future.”*";
P_HTM[10087]="*Atha kho bhagavā tassa purisassa anupubbiṃ kathaṃ kathesi, seyyathidaṃ—**The Buddha then gave him a progressive talk—*";
P_HTM[10088]="*dānakathaṃ sīlakathaṃ saggakathaṃ, kāmānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṅkilesaṃ, nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ pakāsesi.**on generosity, morality, and heaven; on the danger, degradation, and defilement of worldly pleasures; and he revealed the benefits of renunciation.*";
P_HTM[10089]="*Yadā taṃ bhagavā aññāsi kallacittaṃ, muducittaṃ, vinīvaraṇacittaṃ, udaggacittaṃ, pasannacittaṃ, atha yā buddhānaṃ sāmukkaṃsikā dhammadesanā taṃ pakāsesi—**When the Buddha knew that his mind was ready, supple, without hindrances, joyful, and confident, he revealed the teaching unique to the Buddhas:*";
P_HTM[10090]="*dukkhaṃ, samudayaṃ, nirodhaṃ, maggaṃ.**suffering, its origin, its end, and the path.*";
P_HTM[10091]="*Seyyathāpi nāma suddhaṃ vatthaṃ apagatakāḷakaṃ sammadeva rajanaṃ paṭiggaheyya;**And just as a clean and stainless cloth absorbs dye properly,*";
P_HTM[10092]="*evameva tassa purisassa tasmiṃyeva āsane virajaṃ vītamalaṃ dhammacakkhuṃ udapādi—**so too, while he was sitting right there that man experienced the stainless vision of the Truth:*";
P_HTM[10093]="*“yaṃ kiñci samudayadhammaṃ sabbaṃ taṃ nirodhadhamman”ti.**“Anything that has a beginning has an end.”*";
P_HTM[10094]="*Atha kho so puriso diṭṭhadhammo pattadhammo viditadhammo pariyogāḷhadhammo tiṇṇavicikiccho vigatakathaṅkatho vesārajjappatto aparappaccayo satthusāsane bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**He had seen the Truth, had reached, understood, and penetrated it. He had gone beyond doubt and uncertainty, had attained to confidence, and had become independent of others in the Teacher’s instruction. And he said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[10095]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante.**“Wonderful, Sir, wonderful!*";
P_HTM[10096]="*Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya—**Just as one might set upright what had been overturned, or reveal what was hidden, or show the way to one who was lost, or bring a lamp into the darkness*";
P_HTM[10097]="*‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti—**so that one with eyes might see what’s there—*";
P_HTM[10098]="*evamevaṃ bhagavatā anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**just so has the Buddha made the Teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[10099]="*Esāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi, dhammañca, bhikkhusaṅghañca.**I go for refuge to the Buddha, the Teaching, and the Sangha of monks.*";
P_HTM[10100]="*Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**Please accept me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[10101]="*Atha kho bhagavā taṃ purisaṃ etadavoca—**The Buddha then said to him,*";
P_HTM[10102]="*“mā kho tvaṃ, āvuso, iminā maggena gaccha, iminā maggena gacchāhī”ti aññena maggena uyyojesi.**“Don’t go back along this path, go along that one.” And he sent him down a different path.*";
P_HTM[10103]="*Atha kho te dve purisā—**The two men thought,*";
P_HTM[10104]="*“kiṃ nu kho so eko puriso cirena āgacchatī”ti—**“Why is it taking that one man so long to arrive?”*";
P_HTM[10105]="*paṭipathaṃ gacchantā addasāsuṃ bhagavantaṃ aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle nisinnaṃ.**As they were walking along that path in the opposite direction, they saw the Buddha seated at the foot of a tree.*";
P_HTM[10106]="*Disvāna yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu.**They approached him, bowed, and sat down.*";
P_HTM[10107]="*Tesaṃ bhagavā anupubbiṃ kathaṃ kathesi …pe…**And the Buddha gave them a progressive talk …*";
P_HTM[10108]="*aparappaccayā satthusāsane bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ—**and they had become independent of others in the Teacher’s instruction. They then said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[10109]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bhante …pe…**“Wonderful, Sir …*";
P_HTM[10110]="*upāsake no bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gate”ti.**Please accept us as lay followers who have gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[10111]="*Atha kho bhagavā te purise etadavoca—**The Buddha then said to them,*";
P_HTM[10112]="*“mā kho tumhe, āvuso, iminā maggena gacchittha, iminā maggena gacchathā”ti aññena maggena uyyojesi.**“Don’t go back along this path, go along that one.” And he sent them down a different path.*";
P_HTM[10113]="*Atha kho te cattāro purisā …pe…**The four men …*";
P_HTM[10114]="*atha kho te aṭṭha purisā …pe…**the eight men …*";
P_HTM[10115]="*atha kho te soḷasa purisā—**the sixteen men thought,*";
P_HTM[10116]="*kiṃ nu kho te aṭṭha purisā cirena āgacchantīti—**“Why is it taking those eight men so long to arrive?”*";
P_HTM[10117]="*paṭipathaṃ gacchantā addasāsuṃ bhagavantaṃ aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle nisinnaṃ.**As they were walking along that path in the opposite direction, they saw the Buddha seated at the foot of a tree.*";
P_HTM[10118]="*Disvāna yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu.**They approached him, bowed, and sat down.*";
P_HTM[10119]="*Tesaṃ bhagavā anupubbiṃ kathaṃ kathesi, seyyathidaṃ—**And the Buddha gave them a progressive talk …*";
P_HTM[10120]="*dānakathaṃ …pe…* **";
P_HTM[10121]="*aparappaccayā satthusāsane bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ—**and they had become independent of others in the Teacher’s instruction. They then said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[10122]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bhante …pe…**“Wonderful, Sir …*";
P_HTM[10123]="*upāsake no bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gate”ti.**Please accept us as lay followers who have gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[10124]="*Atha kho bhagavā te purise etadavoca—* **";
P_HTM[10125]="*“mā kho tumhe, āvuso, iminā maggena gacchittha, iminā maggena gacchathā”ti aññena maggena uyyojesi.* **";
P_HTM[10126]="*Atha kho so eko puriso yena devadatto tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā devadattaṃ etadavoca—**Soon afterwards that one man went to Devadatta and said,*";
P_HTM[10127]="*“nāhaṃ, bhante, sakkomi taṃ bhagavantaṃ jīvitā voropetuṃ;**“I wasn’t able to kill him, Sir.*";
P_HTM[10128]="*mahiddhiko so bhagavā mahānubhāvo”ti.**He’s powerful and mighty that Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[10129]="*“Alaṃ, āvuso;**“Forget it.*";
P_HTM[10130]="*mā tvaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ jīvitā voropesi.**Don’t kill the ascetic Gotama.*";
P_HTM[10131]="*Ahameva samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ jīvitā voropessāmī”ti.**I’ll do it myself.”*";
P_HTM[10132]="*4. Lohituppādakakamma**2.4 The act of causing the Buddha to bleed*";
P_HTM[10133]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā gijjhakūṭassa pabbatassa chāyāyaṃ caṅkamati.**Soon afterwards the Buddha doing walking meditation in the shade of the Vulture Peak.*";
P_HTM[10134]="*Atha kho devadatto gijjhakūṭaṃ pabbataṃ āruhitvā mahatiṃ silaṃ pavijjhi—**Devadatta climbed the peak and threw down a large stone, thinking,*";
P_HTM[10135]="*imāya samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ jīvitā voropessāmīti.**“With this I’ll kill the ascetic Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[10136]="*Dve pabbatakūṭā samāgantvā taṃ silaṃ sampaṭicchiṃsu.**But the stone got stuck in the junction of two outcrops.*";
P_HTM[10137]="*Tato papatikā uppatitvā bhagavato pāde ruhiraṃ uppādesi.**A chip flew off, hitting the Buddha’s foot and causing it to bleed.*";
P_HTM[10138]="*Atha kho bhagavā uddhaṃ ulloketvā devadattaṃ etadavoca—**The Buddha looked up and said to Devadatta,*";
P_HTM[10139]="*“bahuṃ tayā, moghapurisa, apuññaṃ pasutaṃ, yaṃ tvaṃ duṭṭhacitto vadhakacitto tathāgatassa ruhiraṃ uppādesī”ti.**“Foolish man, you have made much demerit. With an evil mind intent on murder you have made the Buddha bleed.”*";
P_HTM[10140]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[10141]="*“idaṃ, bhikkhave, devadattena paṭhamaṃ ānantariyaṃ kammaṃ upacitaṃ, yaṃ duṭṭhacittena vadhakacittena tathāgatassa ruhiraṃ uppāditan”ti.**“With an evil mind intent on murder Devadatta has made the Buddha bleed. This is his first action with immediate results.”*";
P_HTM[10142]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū—**When the monks heard*";
P_HTM[10143]="*“devadattena kira bhagavato vadho payutto”ti.**that Devadatta was trying to murder the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[10144]="*Te ca bhikkhū bhagavato vihārassa parito parito caṅkamanti uccāsaddā mahāsaddā sajjhāyaṃ karontā, bhagavato rakkhāvaraṇaguttiyā.**they walked back and forth on all sides of the Buddha’s dwelling, trying to protect the Buddha by reciting loudly.*";
P_HTM[10145]="*Assosi kho bhagavā uccāsaddaṃ mahāsaddaṃ sajjhāyasaddaṃ.**The Buddha heard that loud sound of recitation.*";
P_HTM[10146]="*Sutvāna āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi—**He asked Ānanda what it was*";
P_HTM[10147]="*“kiṃ nu kho so, ānanda, uccāsaddo mahāsaddo sajjhāyasaddo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[10148]="*“Assosuṃ kho, bhante, bhikkhū—**and Ānanda told him.*";
P_HTM[10149]="*‘devadattena kira bhagavato vadho payutto’ti.* **";
P_HTM[10150]="*Te ca, bhante, bhikkhū bhagavato vihārassa parito parito caṅkamanti uccāsaddā mahāsaddā sajjhāyaṃ karontā, bhagavato rakkhāvaraṇaguttiyā.* **";
P_HTM[10151]="*So eso, bhagavā, uccāsaddo mahāsaddo sajjhāyasaddo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10152]="*“Tena hānanda, mama vacanena te bhikkhū āmantehi—**The Buddha said, “Well then, Ānanda, tell those monks in my name*";
P_HTM[10153]="*satthā āyasmante āmantetī”ti.**that the Teacher is calling them.”*";
P_HTM[10154]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paṭissutvā yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū etadavoca—**Saying, “Yes, Sir,” he did just that.*";
P_HTM[10155]="*“satthā āyasmante āmantetī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10156]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato ānandassa paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu.**The monks consented. They then went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down.*";
P_HTM[10157]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho te bhikkhū bhagavā etadavoca—**The Buddha said to them,*";
P_HTM[10158]="*“Aṭṭhānametaṃ, bhikkhave, anavakāso, yaṃ parūpakkamena tathāgataṃ jīvitā voropeyya.**“It’s impossible, monks, for anyone to kill me through an act of violence.*";
P_HTM[10159]="*Anupakkamena, bhikkhave, tathāgatā parinibbāyanti.**The Buddha will not attain final extinguishment through an act of violence.*";
P_HTM[10160]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, satthāro santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Monks, there are five kinds of teachers in the world.*";
P_HTM[10161]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[10162]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco satthā aparisuddhasīlo samāno ‘parisuddhasīlomhī’ti paṭijānāti ‘parisuddhaṃ me sīlaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhan’ti ca.**One kind of teacher is impure in behavior, while claiming it is pure.*";
P_HTM[10163]="*Tamenaṃ sāvakā evaṃ jānanti—**His disciples know about his impure behavior,*";
P_HTM[10164]="*‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā aparisuddhasīlo samāno “parisuddhasīlomhī”ti paṭijānāti “parisuddhaṃ me sīlaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhan”ti ca.* **";
P_HTM[10165]="*Mayañceva kho pana gihīnaṃ āroceyyāma, nāssassa manāpaṃ.**but think, ‘It would be unpleasant for him if we inform the householders.*";
P_HTM[10166]="*Yaṃ kho panassa amanāpaṃ, kathaṃ naṃ mayaṃ tena samudācareyyāma?* **";
P_HTM[10167]="*Sammannati kho pana cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena—**Yet it’s because of him that we’re honored with gifts of robes, almsfood, dwellings, and medicines. How then can we inform them?*";
P_HTM[10168]="*yaṃ tumo karissati, tumova tena paññāyissatī’ti.**He will be known through his own actions.’*";
P_HTM[10169]="*Evarūpaṃ kho, bhikkhave, satthāraṃ sāvakā sīlato rakkhanti;**The disciples conceal the impure behavior of such a teacher.*";
P_HTM[10170]="*evarūpo ca pana satthā sāvakehi sīlato rakkhaṃ paccāsīsati.**And the teacher expects his disciples to conceal it.*";
P_HTM[10171]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco satthā aparisuddhājīvo samāno …pe…**Another kind of teacher is impure in livelihood …*";
P_HTM[10172]="*aparisuddhadhammadesano samāno …pe…**gives impure teachings …*";
P_HTM[10173]="*aparisuddhaveyyākaraṇo samāno …pe…**gives impure explanations …*";
P_HTM[10174]="*aparisuddhañāṇadassano samāno ‘parisuddhañāṇadassanomhī’ti paṭijānāti ‘parisuddhaṃ me ñāṇadassanaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhan’ti ca.**has impure knowledge and vision, while claiming they are pure.*";
P_HTM[10175]="*Tamenaṃ sāvakā evaṃ jānanti—**His disciples know about his impure knowledge and vision,*";
P_HTM[10176]="*‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā aparisuddhañāṇadassano samāno “parisuddhañāṇadassanomhī”ti paṭijānāti “parisuddhaṃ me ñāṇadassanaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhan”ti ca.* **";
P_HTM[10177]="*Mayañceva kho pana gihīnaṃ āroceyyāma, nāssassa manāpaṃ.**but think, ‘It would be unpleasant for him if we inform the householders.*";
P_HTM[10178]="*Yaṃ kho panassa amanāpaṃ, kathaṃ na mayaṃ tena samudācareyyāma?* **";
P_HTM[10179]="*Sammannati kho pana cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena—**Yet it’s because of him that we’re honored with gifts of robes, almsfood, dwellings, and medicines. How then can we inform them?*";
P_HTM[10180]="*yaṃ tumo karissati, tumova tena paññāyissatī’ti.**He will be known through his own actions.’*";
P_HTM[10181]="*Evarūpaṃ kho, bhikkhave, satthāraṃ sāvakā ñāṇadassanato rakkhanti;**The disciples conceal the impure knowledge and vision of such a teacher.*";
P_HTM[10182]="*evarūpo ca pana satthā sāvakehi ñāṇadassanato rakkhaṃ paccāsīsati.**And the teacher expects his disciples to conceal it.*";
P_HTM[10183]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca satthāro santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10184]="*Ahaṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, parisuddhasīlo samāno ‘parisuddhasīlomhī’ti paṭijānāmi ‘parisuddhaṃ me sīlaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhan’ti ca.**But in my case, I claim my behavior is pure because it is.*";
P_HTM[10185]="*Na ca maṃ sāvakā sīlato rakkhanti;**My disciples don’t conceal my behavior*";
P_HTM[10186]="*na cāhaṃ sāvakehi sīlato rakkhaṃ paccāsīsāmi.**and I don’t expect them to do so.*";
P_HTM[10187]="*Ahaṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, parisuddhājīvo samāno …pe…**I claim my livelihood is pure …*";
P_HTM[10188]="*parisuddhadhammadesano samāno …pe…**I claim my teachings are pure …*";
P_HTM[10189]="*parisuddhaveyyākaraṇo samāno …pe…**I claim my explanations are pure …*";
P_HTM[10190]="*parisuddhañāṇadassano samāno “parisuddhañāṇadassanomhī”ti paṭijānāmi “parisuddhaṃ me ñāṇadassanaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhan”ti ca, na ca maṃ sāvakā ñāṇadassanato rakkhanti, na cāhaṃ sāvakehi ñāṇadassanato rakkhaṃ paccāsīsāmi.**I claim my knowledge and vision are pure because they are. My disciples don’t conceal my knowledge and vision and I don’t expect them to do so.*";
P_HTM[10191]="*“Aṭṭhānametaṃ, bhikkhave, anavakāso, yaṃ parūpakkamena tathāgataṃ jīvitā voropeyya.**It’s impossible for anyone to kill me through an act of violence.*";
P_HTM[10192]="*Anupakkamena, bhikkhave, tathāgatā parinibbāyanti.**The Buddha will not attain final extinguishment through an act of violence.*";
P_HTM[10193]="*Gacchatha tumhe, bhikkhave, yathāvihāraṃ.**Go to your dwellings, monks.*";
P_HTM[10194]="*Arakkhiyā, bhikkhave, tathāgatā”ti.**I don’t need any protection.”*";
P_HTM[10195]="*5. Nāḷāgiripesana**2.5 The letting loose of Nāḷāgiri*";
P_HTM[10196]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājagahe nāḷāgiri nāma hatthī caṇḍo hoti, manussaghātako.**At that time in Rājagaha there was a violent elephant called Nāḷāgiri, a killer of humans.*";
P_HTM[10197]="*Atha kho devadatto rājagahaṃ pavisitvā hatthisālaṃ gantvā hatthibhaṇḍe etadavoca—**Devadatta then entered Rājagaha, went to the elephant stables, and said to the elephant keepers,*";
P_HTM[10198]="*“mayaṃ kho, bhaṇe, rājañātakā nāma paṭibalā nīcaṭṭhāniyaṃ uccaṭṭhāne ṭhapetuṃ, bhattampi vetanampi vaḍḍhāpetuṃ.**“We who are relatives of the King are capable of having people promoted and getting them a raise.*";
P_HTM[10199]="*Tena hi, bhaṇe, yadā samaṇo gotamo imaṃ racchaṃ paṭipanno hoti, tadā imaṃ nāḷāgiriṃ hatthiṃ muñcetvā imaṃ racchaṃ paṭipādethā”ti.**So then, when the ascetic Gotama comes walking along this street, release the elephant Nāḷāgiri down this same street.”*";
P_HTM[10200]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te hatthibhaṇḍā devadattassa paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10201]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ rājagahaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**One morning soon afterwards, the Buddha robed up, took his bowl and robe, and entered Rājagaha for alms together with a number of monks.*";
P_HTM[10202]="*Atha kho bhagavā taṃ racchaṃ paṭipajji.**And the Buddha walked down that very street.*";
P_HTM[10203]="*Addasāsuṃ kho te hatthibhaṇḍā bhagavantaṃ taṃ racchaṃ paṭipannaṃ.**When the elephant keepers saw the Buddha coming,*";
P_HTM[10204]="*Disvāna nāḷāgiriṃ hatthiṃ muñcitvā taṃ racchaṃ paṭipādesuṃ.**they released Nāḷāgiri down the same street.*";
P_HTM[10205]="*Addasā kho nāḷāgiri hatthī bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**Nāḷāgiri saw the Buddha coming.*";
P_HTM[10206]="*Disvāna soṇḍaṃ ussāpetvā pahaṭṭhakaṇṇavālo yena bhagavā tena abhidhāvi.**He blew his trunk, and with ears and tail bristling, he charged toward the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[10207]="*Addasāsuṃ kho te bhikkhū nāḷāgiriṃ hatthiṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**When the monks saw Nāḷāgiri coming,*";
P_HTM[10208]="*Disvāna bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ—**they said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[10209]="*“ayaṃ, bhante, nāḷāgiri hatthī caṇḍo manussaghātako imaṃ racchaṃ paṭipanno.**“This elephant coming down the street is Nāḷāgiri, a violent killer of humans.*";
P_HTM[10210]="*Paṭikkamatu, bhante, bhagavā;**Please retreat, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10211]="*paṭikkamatu sugato”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10212]="*“Āgacchatha, bhikkhave, mā bhāyittha.**“Come, don’t be afraid.*";
P_HTM[10213]="*Aṭṭhānametaṃ, bhikkhave, anavakāso, yaṃ parūpakkamena tathāgataṃ jīvitā voropeyya.**It’s impossible for anyone to kill the Buddha through an act of violence.*";
P_HTM[10214]="*Anupakkamena, bhikkhave, tathāgatā parinibbāyantī”ti.**The Buddha will not attain final extinguishment through an act of violence.”*";
P_HTM[10215]="*Dutiyampi kho te bhikkhū …pe…**A second time*";
P_HTM[10216]="*tatiyampi kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ—**and a third time those monks said the same thing to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[10217]="*“ayaṃ, bhante, nāḷāgiri hatthī caṇḍo manussaghātako imaṃ racchaṃ paṭipanno.* **";
P_HTM[10218]="*Paṭikkamatu, bhante, bhagavā;* **";
P_HTM[10219]="*paṭikkamatu sugato”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10220]="*“Āgacchatha, bhikkhave, mā bhāyittha.**each time getting the same reply.*";
P_HTM[10221]="*Aṭṭhānametaṃ, bhikkhave, anavakāso, yaṃ parūpakkamena tathāgataṃ jīvitā voropeyya.* **";
P_HTM[10222]="*Anupakkamena, bhikkhave, tathāgatā parinibbāyantī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10223]="*Tena kho pana samayena manussā pāsādesupi hammiyesupi chadanesupi āruḷhā acchanti.**On that occasion people had ascended their stilt houses and even their roofs.*";
P_HTM[10224]="*Tattha ye te manussā assaddhā appasannā dubbuddhino, te evamāhaṃsu—**The foolish people with little faith and confidence said,*";
P_HTM[10225]="*“abhirūpo vata, bho, mahāsamaṇo nāgena viheṭhīyissatī”ti.**“The elephant will hurt the handsome great ascetic.”*";
P_HTM[10226]="*Ye pana te manussā saddhā pasannā paṇḍitā byattā buddhimanto, te evamāhaṃsu—**But the wise people with faith and confidence said,*";
P_HTM[10227]="*“nacirassaṃ vata, bho, nāgo nāgena saṅgāmessatī”ti.**“Soon the great man and the great elephant will meet in battle.”*";
P_HTM[10228]="*Atha kho bhagavā nāḷāgiriṃ hatthiṃ mettena cittena phari.**The Buddha then pervaded Nāḷāgiri with a mind of love.*";
P_HTM[10229]="*Atha kho nāḷāgiri hatthī bhagavato mettena cittena phuṭṭho soṇḍaṃ oropetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato purato aṭṭhāsi.**Feeling it, Nāḷāgiri lowered his trunk, went up to the Buddha, and stood in front of him.*";
P_HTM[10230]="*Atha kho bhagavā dakkhiṇena hatthena nāḷāgirissa hatthissa kumbhaṃ parāmasanto nāḷāgiriṃ hatthiṃ imāhi gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi—**And while stroking Nāḷāgiri on the forehead with his right hand, the Buddha spoke these verses:*";
P_HTM[10231]="*“Mā kuñjara nāgamāsado,**“Do not, elephant, attack a great man;*";
P_HTM[10232]="*Dukkhañhi kuñjara nāgamāsado;**Painful it is to attack a great man.*";
P_HTM[10233]="*Na hi nāgahatassa kuñjara,**For a killer of a great man,*";
P_HTM[10234]="*Sugati hoti ito paraṃ yato.**The next rebirth is not good.*";
P_HTM[10235]="*Mā ca mado mā ca pamādo,**Don’t be intoxicated or heedless,*";
P_HTM[10236]="*Na hi pamattā sugatiṃ vajanti te;**For the heedless are not reborn well.*";
P_HTM[10237]="*Tvaññeva tathā karissasi,**Only do those things*";
P_HTM[10238]="*Yena tvaṃ sugatiṃ gamissasī”ti.**That will take you to a good rebirth.”*";
P_HTM[10239]="*Atha kho nāḷāgiri hatthī soṇḍāya bhagavato pādapaṃsūni gahetvā uparimuddhani ākiritvā paṭikuṭiyova osakki, yāva bhagavantaṃ addakkhi.**Nāḷāgiri sucked the dust from the Buddha’s feet with his trunk and scattered it overhead. He then walked backward while looking at the Buddha*";
P_HTM[10240]="*Atha kho nāḷāgiri hatthī hatthisālaṃ gantvā sake ṭhāne aṭṭhāsi.**and returned to his own spot in the elephant stables.*";
P_HTM[10241]="*Tathā danto ca pana nāḷāgiri hatthī ahosi.**That is how tame Nāḷāgiri had become.*";
P_HTM[10242]="*Tena kho pana samayena manussā imaṃ gāthaṃ gāyanti—**On that occasion people chanted this verse:*";
P_HTM[10243]="*“Daṇḍeneke damayanti,**“Some are tamed with sticks*";
P_HTM[10244]="*aṅkusehi kasāhi ca;**And with goads and whips.*";
P_HTM[10245]="*Adaṇḍena asatthena,**Without stick or sword,*";
P_HTM[10246]="*nāgo danto mahesinā”ti.**The great sage tamed the elephant.”*";
P_HTM[10247]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**And people complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[10248]="*“yāva pāpo ayaṃ devadatto, alakkhiko, yatra hi nāma samaṇassa gotamassa evaṃmahiddhikassa evaṃmahānubhāvassa vadhāya parakkamissatī”ti.**“How evil he is this Devadatta, how benighted, in that he tries to kill the ascetic Gotama so powerful and mighty.”*";
P_HTM[10249]="*Devadattassa lābhasakkāro parihāyi.**Devadatta’s gain and honor declined,*";
P_HTM[10250]="*Bhagavato ca lābhasakkāro abhivaḍḍhi.**whereas those of the Buddha increased.*";
P_HTM[10251]="*6. Pañcavatthuyācanakathā**2.6 The account of the request for the five points*";
P_HTM[10252]="*Tena kho pana samayena devadatto parihīnalābhasakkāro sapariso kulesu viññāpetvā viññāpetvā bhuñjati.**Because of decline in material support and loss of respect, Devadatta and his followers were only invited to meals after repeatedly asking.*";
P_HTM[10253]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10254]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā kulesu viññāpetvā viññāpetvā bhuñjissanti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics eat at invitations after repeatedly asking?*";
P_HTM[10255]="*Kassa sampannaṃ na manāpaṃ, kassa sāduṃ na ruccatī”ti.**Who doesn’t like nice food? Who doesn’t prefer tasty food?”*";
P_HTM[10256]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[10257]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[10258]="*“kathañhi nāma devadatto sapariso kulesu viññāpetvā viññāpetvā bhuñjissatī”ti.**“How can Devadatta and his followers eat at invitations after repeatedly asking?”*";
P_HTM[10259]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned Devadatta:*";
P_HTM[10260]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, devadatta, sapariso kulesu viññāpetvā viññāpetvā bhuñjasī”ti?**“Is it true, Devadatta, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[10261]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[10262]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**After rebuking him …*";
P_HTM[10263]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[10264]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ kulesu tikabhojanaṃ paññapessāmi tayo atthavase paṭicca—**“Well then, for monks eating among families I’ll lay down a rule against eating in groups of more than three, for these three reasons:*";
P_HTM[10265]="*dummaṅkūnaṃ puggalānaṃ niggahāya;**for the restraint of bad people;*";
P_HTM[10266]="*pesalānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ phāsuvihārāya, ‘mā pāpicchā pakkhaṃ nissāya saṅghaṃ bhindeyyun’ti;**for the ease of good monks, stopping those with bad desires from creating a faction and then splitting the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[10267]="*kulānuddayāya ca.**and out of compassion for families.*";
P_HTM[10268]="*Gaṇabhojane yathādhammo kāretabbo”ti.**Anyone eating in a group is to be dealt with according to the rule.”*";
P_HTM[10269]="*Atha kho devadatto yena kokāliko kaṭamodakatissako khaṇḍadeviyā putto samuddadatto tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā kokālikaṃ kaṭamodakatissakaṃ khaṇḍadeviyā puttaṃ samuddadattaṃ etadavoca—**Soon afterwards Devadatta went to see Kokālika, Kaṭamodakatissaka, Khaṇḍadeviyā-putta, and Samuddadatta, and he said to them,*";
P_HTM[10270]="*“etha, mayaṃ, āvuso, samaṇassa gotamassa saṅghabhedaṃ karissāma cakkabhedan”ti.**“Let’s create a schism in the Sangha of the ascetic Gotama. Let’s break its authority.”*";
P_HTM[10271]="*Evaṃ vutte, kokāliko devadattaṃ etadavoca—**Kokālika said to Devadatta,*";
P_HTM[10272]="*“samaṇo kho, āvuso, gotamo mahiddhiko mahānubhāvo.**“The ascetic Gotama is powerful and mighty.*";
P_HTM[10273]="*Kathaṃ mayaṃ samaṇassa gotamassa saṅghabhedaṃ karissāma cakkabhedan”ti?**How can we achieve this?”*";
P_HTM[10274]="*“Etha, mayaṃ, āvuso, samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ upasaṅkamitvā pañca vatthūni yācissāma—**“Well, let’s go to the ascetic Gotama and request five things:*";
P_HTM[10275]="*‘bhagavā, bhante, anekapariyāyena appicchassa santuṭṭhassa sallekhassa dhutassa pāsādikassa apacayassa vīriyārambhassa vaṇṇavādī.**‘In many ways, Sir, you praise fewness of wishes, contentment, the erasing of defilements, ascetic practices, being inspiring, the reduction in things, and being energetic.*";
P_HTM[10276]="*Imāni, bhante, pañca vatthūni anekapariyāyena appicchatāya santuṭṭhiyā sallekhāya dhutatāya pāsādikatāya apacayāya vīriyārambhāya saṃvattanti.**And there are five things that lead to just that.*";
P_HTM[10277]="*Sādhu, bhante, bhikkhū yāvajīvaṃ āraññikā assu; yo gāmantaṃ osareyya, vajjaṃ naṃ phuseyya.**It would be good, Sir, if the monks stayed in the wilderness for life, and whoever stays near an inhabited area would commit an offense;*";
P_HTM[10278]="*Yāvajīvaṃ piṇḍapātikā assu; yo nimantanaṃ sādiyeyya, vajjaṃ naṃ phuseyya.**if they ate only almsfood for life, and whoever accepts an invitational meal would commit an offense;*";
P_HTM[10279]="*Yāvajīvaṃ paṃsukūlikā assu; yo gahapaticīvaraṃ sādiyeyya, vajjaṃ naṃ phuseyya.**if they wore rag-robes for life, and whoever accepts a robe from a householder would commit an offense;*";
P_HTM[10280]="*Yāvajīvaṃ rukkhamūlikā assu; yo channaṃ upagaccheyya, vajjaṃ naṃ phuseyya.**if they live at the foot of a tree for life, and whoever takes shelter would commit an offense;*";
P_HTM[10281]="*Yāvajīvaṃ macchamaṃsaṃ na khādeyyuṃ; yo macchamaṃsaṃ khādeyya, vajjaṃ naṃ phuseyyā’ti.**if they didn’t eat fish or meat for life, and whoever does would commit an offense.’*";
P_HTM[10282]="*Imāni pañca vatthūni samaṇo gotamo nānujānissati.**The ascetic Gotama won’t allow this.*";
P_HTM[10283]="*Te mayaṃ imehi pañcahi vatthūhi janaṃ saññāpessāmā”ti.**We’ll then be able to win people over with these five points.”*";
P_HTM[10284]="*“Sakkā kho, āvuso, imehi pañcahi vatthūhi samaṇassa gotamassa saṅghabhedo kātuṃ cakkabhedo.**Kokālika said, “It might be possible to create a schism in the Sangha with these five points,*";
P_HTM[10285]="*Lūkhappasannā hi, āvuso, manussā”ti.**for people have confidence in austerity.”*";
P_HTM[10286]="*Atha kho devadatto sapariso yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Devadatta and his followers then went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[10287]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho devadatto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and Devadatta made his request.*";
P_HTM[10288]="*“bhagavā, bhante, anekapariyāyena appicchassa santuṭṭhassa sallekhassa dhutassa pāsādikassa apacayassa vīriyārambhassa vaṇṇavādī.* **";
P_HTM[10289]="*Imāni, bhante, pañca vatthūni anekapariyāyena appicchatāya santuṭṭhiyā sallekhāya dhutatāya pāsādikatāya apacayāya vīriyārambhāya saṃvattanti.* **";
P_HTM[10290]="*Sādhu, bhante, bhikkhū yāvajīvaṃ āraññikā assu; yo gāmantaṃ osareyya, vajjaṃ naṃ phuseyya.* **";
P_HTM[10291]="*Yāvajīvaṃ piṇḍapātikā assu; yo nimantanaṃ sādiyeyya, vajjaṃ naṃ phuseyya.* **";
P_HTM[10292]="*Yāvajīvaṃ paṃsukūlikā assu; yo gahapaticīvaraṃ sādiyeyya, vajjaṃ naṃ phuseyya.* **";
P_HTM[10293]="*Yāvajīvaṃ rukkhamūlikā assu; yo channaṃ upagaccheyya, vajjaṃ naṃ phuseyya.* **";
P_HTM[10294]="*Yāvajīvaṃ macchamaṃsaṃ na khādeyyuṃ; yo macchamaṃsaṃ khādeyya, vajjaṃ naṃ phuseyyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10295]="*“Alaṃ, devadatta.**The Buddha replied, “No, Devadatta.*";
P_HTM[10296]="*Yo icchati, āraññiko hotu; yo icchati, gāmante viharatu.**Those who wish may stay in the wilderness and those who wish may live near an inhabited area.*";
P_HTM[10297]="*Yo icchati, piṇḍapātiko hotu; yo icchati, nimantanaṃ sādiyatu.**Those who wish may eat only almsfood and those who wish may accept invitations.*";
P_HTM[10298]="*Yo icchati, paṃsukūliko hotu; yo icchati, gahapaticīvaraṃ sādiyatu.**Those who wish may wear rag-robes and those who wish may accept robes from householders.*";
P_HTM[10299]="*Aṭṭhamāse kho mayā, devadatta, rukkhamūlasenāsanaṃ anuññātaṃ;**I have allowed the foot of a tree as resting place for eight months of the year,*";
P_HTM[10300]="*tikoṭiparisuddhaṃ macchamaṃsaṃ—**as well as fish and meat that are pure in three respects:*";
P_HTM[10301]="*adiṭṭhaṃ, assutaṃ, aparisaṅkitan”ti.**one hasn’t seen, heard, or suspected that the animal was specifically killed to feed a monastic.”*";
P_HTM[10302]="*Atha kho devadatto—**Devadatta thought,*";
P_HTM[10303]="*“na bhagavā imāni pañca vatthūni anujānātī”ti—**“The Buddha doesn’t allow the five points,”*";
P_HTM[10304]="*haṭṭho udaggo sapariso uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**and he was glad and elated. He got up from his seat, bowed down, circumambulated the Buddha with his right side toward him, and left with his followers.*";
P_HTM[10305]="*Atha kho devadatto sapariso rājagahaṃ pavisitvā pañcahi vatthūhi janaṃ saññāpesi—**Devadatta then entered Rājagaha and won people over with the five points,*";
P_HTM[10306]="*“mayaṃ, āvuso, samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ upasaṅkamitvā pañca vatthūni yācimhā—* **";
P_HTM[10307]="*‘bhagavā, bhante, anekapariyāyena appicchassa …pe…* **";
P_HTM[10308]="*vīriyārambhassa vaṇṇavādī.* **";
P_HTM[10309]="*Imāni, bhante, pañca vatthūni anekapariyāyena appicchatāya …pe…* **";
P_HTM[10310]="*vīriyārambhāya saṃvattanti.* **";
P_HTM[10311]="*Sādhu, bhante, bhikkhū yāvajīvaṃ āraññikā assu; yo gāmantaṃ osareyya, vajjaṃ naṃ phuseyya …pe…* **";
P_HTM[10312]="*yāvajīvaṃ macchamaṃsaṃ na khādeyyuṃ; yo macchamaṃsaṃ khādeyya, vajjaṃ naṃ phuseyyā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[10313]="*Imāni pañca vatthūni samaṇo gotamo nānujānāti.**saying, “The ascetic Gotama doesn’t agree to them,*";
P_HTM[10314]="*Te mayaṃ imehi pañcahi vatthūhi samādāya vattāmā”ti.**but we practice in accordance with them.”*";
P_HTM[10315]="*Tattha ye te manussā assaddhā appasannā dubbuddhino, te evamāhaṃsu—**The foolish people there with little faith and confidence said,*";
P_HTM[10316]="*“ime kho samaṇā sakyaputtiyā dhutā sallekhavuttino.**“These Sakyan monastics are practicing asceticism and they live their lives to erase defilements.*";
P_HTM[10317]="*Samaṇo pana gotamo bāhulliko bāhullāya cetetī”ti.**But the acetic Gotama is extravagant and has chosen to live a life of indulgence.”*";
P_HTM[10318]="*Ye pana te manussā saddhā pasannā paṇḍitā byattā buddhimanto, te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**But the wise people who had faith and confidence complained and criticized Devadatta,*";
P_HTM[10319]="*“kathañhi nāma devadatto bhagavato saṅghabhedāya parakkamissati cakkabhedāyā”ti.**“How can Devadatta pursue schism in the Sangha of the Buddha? How can he break its authority?”*";
P_HTM[10320]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the criticism of those people,*";
P_HTM[10321]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized him in the same way.*";
P_HTM[10322]="*“kathañhi nāma devadatto saṅghabhedāya parakkamissati cakkabhedāyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10323]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They then told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned Devadatta:*";
P_HTM[10324]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, devadatta, saṅghabhedāya parakkamasi cakkabhedāyā”ti?**“Is it true, Devadatta, that you are doing this?”*";
P_HTM[10325]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10326]="*“Alaṃ, devadatta.**“Let it be, Devadatta,*";
P_HTM[10327]="*Mā te rucci saṅghabhedo.**don’t create a schism in the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[10328]="*Garuko kho, devadatta, saṅghabhedo.**Schism in the Sangha is a serious matter.*";
P_HTM[10329]="*Yo kho, devadatta, samaggaṃ saṅghaṃ bhindati, kappaṭṭhikaṃ kibbisaṃ pasavati, kappaṃ nirayamhi paccati.**Whoever creates a schism in a united Sangha, does a bad act with effect for an eon; he is boiled in hell for an eon.*";
P_HTM[10330]="*Yo ca kho, devadatta, bhinnaṃ saṅghaṃ samaggaṃ karoti, brahmaṃ puññaṃ pasavati, kappaṃ saggamhi modati.**But whoever unites a divided Sangha, generates the supreme merit; he rejoices in heaven for an eon.*";
P_HTM[10331]="*Alaṃ, devadatta.**So let it be, Devadatta,*";
P_HTM[10332]="*Mā te rucci saṅghabhedo.**don’t create a schism in the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[10333]="*Garuko kho, devadatta, saṅghabhedo”ti.**Schism in the Sangha is a serious matter.”*";
P_HTM[10334]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya rājagahaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Soon afterwards, after robing up in the morning, Venerable Ānanda took his bowl and robe and entered Rājagaha for alms.*";
P_HTM[10335]="*Addasā kho devadatto āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ rājagahe piṇḍāya carantaṃ.**When Devadatta saw him,*";
P_HTM[10336]="*Disvāna yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca—**he approached him, and said,*";
P_HTM[10337]="*“ajjataggedānāhaṃ, āvuso ānanda, aññatreva bhagavatā, aññatreva bhikkhusaṅghā, uposathaṃ karissāmi saṅghakammaṃ karissāmī”ti.**“From today on, Ānanda, I’ll do the observance-day procedure and the legal procedures of the Sangha separate from the Buddha and the Sangha of monks.”*";
P_HTM[10338]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando rājagahe piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**When Ānanda had walked for alms, after his meal and after returning from almsround, he went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[10339]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and told him what had happened,*";
P_HTM[10340]="*“idhāhaṃ, bhante, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya rājagahaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10341]="*Addasā kho maṃ, bhante, devadatto rājagahe piṇḍāya carantaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[10342]="*Disvāna yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā maṃ etadavoca—* **";
P_HTM[10343]="*‘ajjataggedānāhaṃ, āvuso ānanda, aññatreva bhagavatā, aññatreva bhikkhusaṅghā, uposathaṃ karissāmi saṅghakammaṃ karissāmī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[10344]="*Ajjatagge, bhante, devadatto saṅghaṃ bhindissatī”ti.**adding, “From today, Venerable Sir, Devadatta has created a schism in the Sangha.”*";
P_HTM[10345]="*Atha kho bhagavā etamatthaṃ viditvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ udānaṃ udānesi—**Understanding the significance of this, on that occasion the Buddha uttered a heartfelt exclamation:*";
P_HTM[10346]="*“Sukaraṃ sādhunā sādhuṃ,**“For the good doing good is easy;*";
P_HTM[10347]="*Sādhuṃ pāpena dukkaraṃ;**For the bad doing good is hard;*";
P_HTM[10348]="*Pāpaṃ pāpena sukaraṃ,**For the bad doing evil is easy;*";
P_HTM[10349]="*Pāpamariyehi dukkaran”ti.**For the noble ones doing evil is hard.”*";
P_HTM[10350]="*Dutiyabhāṇavāro niṭṭhito.**The second section for recitation is finished.*";
P_HTM[10351]="*1. Saṅghabhedakathā**3.1 The account of schism in the Sangha*";
P_HTM[10352]="*Atha kho devadatto tadahuposathe uṭṭhāyāsanā salākaṃ gāhesi—**On the observance day soon afterwards, Devadatta got up from his seat and distributed voting tickets, saying,*";
P_HTM[10353]="*“mayaṃ, āvuso, samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ upasaṅkamitvā pañca vatthūni yācimhā—**“We have gone to the ascetic Gotama and asked for five things:*";
P_HTM[10354]="*‘bhagavā, bhante, anekapariyāyena appicchassa …pe…**‘In many ways, Sir, you praiss fewness of wishes, contentment, the erasing of defilements, ascetic practices, being inspiring, the reduction in things,*";
P_HTM[10355]="*vīriyārambhassa vaṇṇavādī.**and being energetic.*";
P_HTM[10356]="*Imāni, bhante, pañca vatthūni anekapariyāyena appicchatāya …pe…**And there are five things that lead to just that.*";
P_HTM[10357]="*vīriyārambhāya saṃvattanti.* **";
P_HTM[10358]="*Sādhu, bhante, bhikkhū yāvajīvaṃ āraññikā assu; yo gāmantaṃ osareyya, vajjaṃ naṃ phuseyya …pe…**It would be good, Sir, if the monks stayed in the wilderness for life, and whoever stays near an inhabited area would commit an offense;*";
P_HTM[10359]="*yāvajīvaṃ macchamaṃsaṃ na khādeyyuṃ; yo macchamaṃsaṃ khādeyya, vajjaṃ naṃ phuseyyā’ti.**if they didn’t eat fish or meat for life, and whoever does would commit an offense.’*";
P_HTM[10360]="*Imāni pañca vatthūni samaṇo gotamo nānujānāti.**The ascetic Gotama doesn’t agree to them,*";
P_HTM[10361]="*Te mayaṃ imehi pañcahi vatthūhi samādāya vattāma.**but we practice in accordance with them.*";
P_HTM[10362]="*Yassāyasmato imāni pañca vatthūni khamanti, so salākaṃ gaṇhātū”ti.**Any monk who approves of these five things should take a voting ticket.”*";
P_HTM[10363]="*Tena kho pana samayena vesālikā vajjiputtakā pañcamattāni bhikkhusatāni navakā ceva honti appakataññuno ca.**On that occasion five hundred Vajjian monks from Vesālī, newly ordained and ignorant, were present.*";
P_HTM[10364]="*Te—“ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanan”ti salākaṃ gaṇhiṃsu.**Thinking, “This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction,” they took voting tickets.*";
P_HTM[10365]="*Atha kho devadatto saṅghaṃ bhinditvā pañcamattāni bhikkhusatāni ādāya yena gayāsīsaṃ tena pakkāmi.**Then, after causing a schism in the Sangha, Devadatta left for Gayāsīsa together with five hundred monks.*";
P_HTM[10366]="*Atha kho sāriputtamoggallānā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu.**Soon afterwards Sāriputta and Moggallāna went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[10367]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[10368]="*“devadatto, bhante, saṅghaṃ bhinditvā pañcamattāni bhikkhusatāni ādāya yena gayāsīsaṃ tena pakkanto”ti.**“Venerable Sir, Devadatta has split the Sangha and left for Gayāsīsa together with five hundred monks.”*";
P_HTM[10369]="*“Na hi nāma tumhākaṃ, sāriputtā, tesu navakesu bhikkhūsu kāruññampi bhavissati?**“You have compassion for those five hundred newly ordained monks, don’t you?*";
P_HTM[10370]="*Gacchatha tumhe, sāriputtā, purā te bhikkhū anayabyasanaṃ āpajjantī”ti.**Go then, Sāriputta and Moggallāna, before they are affected by misfortune and disaster.”*";
P_HTM[10371]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho sāriputtamoggallānā bhagavato paṭissutvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā yena gayāsīsaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu.**Saying, “Yes,” Sāriputta and Moggallāna got up from their seats, bowed down, circumambulated the Buddha with their right side toward him, and went to Gayāsīsa.*";
P_HTM[10372]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu bhagavato avidūre rodamāno ṭhito hoti.**Just then a certain monk who was standing near the Buddha was crying.*";
P_HTM[10373]="*Atha kho bhagavā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—**The Buddha asked him why.*";
P_HTM[10374]="*“kissa tvaṃ, bhikkhu, rodasī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[10375]="*“Yepi te, bhante, bhagavato aggasāvakā sāriputtamoggallānā tepi devadattassa santike gacchanti devadattassa dhammaṃ rocentā”ti.**He replied, “Even Sāriputta and Moggallāna, the Buddha’s chief disciples, are going to Devadatta because they approve of his teaching.”*";
P_HTM[10376]="*“Aṭṭhānametaṃ, bhikkhu, anavakāso, yaṃ sāriputtamoggallānā devadattassa dhammaṃ roceyyuṃ, api ca te gatā bhikkhūnaṃ saññattiyā”ti.**“It’s impossible for Sāriputta and Moggallāna to approve of Devadatta’s teaching. Instead, they’ve gone to win those monks over.”*";
P_HTM[10377]="*Tena kho pana samayena devadatto mahatiyā parisāya parivuto dhammaṃ desento nisinno hoti.**On that occasion Devadatta was seated giving a teaching surrounded by a great gathering.*";
P_HTM[10378]="*Addasā kho devadatto sāriputtamoggallāne dūratova āgacchante.**When Devadatta saw Sāriputta and Moggallāna coming,*";
P_HTM[10379]="*Disvāna bhikkhū āmantesi—**he said to the monks,*";
P_HTM[10380]="*“passatha, bhikkhave, yāva svākkhāto mayā dhammo, yepi te samaṇassa gotamassa aggasāvakā sāriputtamoggallānā tepi mama santike āgacchanti.**“See how well-taught my teaching is, in that even Sāriputta and Moggallāna, the ascetic Gotama’s chief disciples, are coming here*";
P_HTM[10381]="*Mama dhammaṃ rocentā”ti.**because they approve of my teaching.”*";
P_HTM[10382]="*Evaṃ vutte, kokāliko devadattaṃ etadavoca—**But Kokālika said,*";
P_HTM[10383]="*“mā, āvuso devadatta, sāriputtamoggallāne vissasi.**“Don’t trust Sāriputta and Moggallāna.*";
P_HTM[10384]="*Pāpicchā sāriputtamoggallānā, pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gatā”ti.**They have bad desires. They are in the grip of bad desires.”*";
P_HTM[10385]="*“Alaṃ, āvuso.**“Don’t worry.*";
P_HTM[10386]="*Svāgataṃ tesaṃ yato me dhammaṃ rocentī”ti.**Anyone who comes to approve of my teaching is welcome.”*";
P_HTM[10387]="*Atha kho devadatto āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ upaḍḍhāsanena nimantesi—**Devadatta invited Venerable Sāriputta*";
P_HTM[10388]="*“ehāvuso sāriputta, idha nisīdāhī”ti.**to sit on a seat half the height of his own.*";
P_HTM[10389]="*“Alaṃ, āvuso”ti kho āyasmā sāriputto aññataraṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Saying, “There’s no need,” Sāriputta took another seat and sat down to one side,*";
P_HTM[10390]="*Āyasmāpi kho mahāmoggallāno aññataraṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**as did Mahāmoggallāna.*";
P_HTM[10391]="*Atha kho devadatto bahudeva rattiṃ bhikkhū dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ ajjhesi—**After spending most of the night instructing, inspiring, and gladdening the monks with a teaching, Devadatta invited Sāriputta, saying*";
P_HTM[10392]="*“vigatathinamiddho kho, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhusaṅgho.**“The Sangha of monks is without dullness and drowsiness.*";
P_HTM[10393]="*Paṭibhātu taṃ, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhūnaṃ dhammī kathā, piṭṭhi me āgilāyati, tamahaṃ āyamissāmī”ti.**Give a teaching, Sāriputta. My back is aching and I’ll stretch it.”*";
P_HTM[10394]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā sāriputto devadattassa paccassosi.**“Yes.”*";
P_HTM[10395]="*Atha kho devadatto catugguṇaṃ saṅghāṭiṃ paññapetvā dakkhiṇena passena seyyaṃ kappesi.**Devadatta then folded his upper robe in four and lay down on his right side.*";
P_HTM[10396]="*Tassa kilamantassa muṭṭhassatissa asampajānassa muhuttakeneva niddā okkami.**Because he was tired, absentminded, and heedless, he fell asleep in an instant.*";
P_HTM[10397]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto ādesanāpāṭihāriyānusāsaniyā bhikkhū dhammiyā kathāya ovadi anusāsi.**Venerable Sāriputta then used the wonder of mind reading to instruct them,*";
P_HTM[10398]="*Āyasmā mahāmoggallāno iddhipāṭihāriyānusāsaniyā bhikkhū dhammiyā kathāya ovadi anusāsi.**and Venerable Mahāmoggallāna used the wonder of supernormal powers to the same effect.*";
P_HTM[10399]="*Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ āyasmatā sāriputtena ādesanāpāṭihāriyānusāsaniyā āyasmatā ca mahāmoggallānena iddhipāṭihāriyānusāsaniyā ovadiyamānānaṃ anusāsiyamānānaṃ virajaṃ vītamalaṃ dhammacakkhuṃ udapādi—**While those monks were being instructed like this, they experienced the stainless vision of the Truth:*";
P_HTM[10400]="*“yaṃ kiñci samudayadhammaṃ sabbaṃ taṃ nirodhadhamman”ti.**“Anything that has a beginning has an end.”*";
P_HTM[10401]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi—**And Sāriputta addressed those monks:*";
P_HTM[10402]="*“gacchāma mayaṃ, āvuso, bhagavato santike.**“Let’s go to the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[10403]="*Yo tassa bhagavato dhammaṃ rocesi so āgacchatū”ti.**Whoever approves of the teaching of the Buddha should come along.”*";
P_HTM[10404]="*Atha kho sāriputtamoggallānā tāni pañcabhikkhusatāni ādāya yena veḷuvanaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu.**Sāriputta and Moggallāna then went to the Bamboo Grove accompanied by those five hundred monks.*";
P_HTM[10405]="*Atha kho kokāliko devadattaṃ uṭṭhāpesi—**In the meantime Kokālika woke up Devadatta, saying,*";
P_HTM[10406]="*“uṭṭhehi, āvuso devadatta, nītā te bhikkhū sāriputtamoggallānehi.**“Get up, Devadatta, your monks are being led away by Sāriputta and Moggallāna.*";
P_HTM[10407]="*Nanu tvaṃ, āvuso devadatta, mayā vutto—**Didn’t I tell you*";
P_HTM[10408]="*‘mā, āvuso devadatta, sāriputtamoggallāne vissāsi.**not to trust Sāriputta and Moggallāna?*";
P_HTM[10409]="*Pāpicchā sāriputtamoggallānā, pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gatā’”ti?**Didn’t I say that they have bad desires, that they are in the grip of bad desires?”*";
P_HTM[10410]="*Atha kho devadattassa tattheva uṇhaṃ lohitaṃ mukhato uggañchi.**And Devadatta vomited hot blood right there.*";
P_HTM[10411]="*Atha kho sāriputtamoggallānā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdisuṃ.**But Sāriputta and Moggallāna went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[10412]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[10413]="*“sādhu, bhante, bhedakānuvattakā bhikkhū puna upasampajjeyyun”ti.**“Venerable Sir, it would be good if we could reordain the monks who sided with the schism.”*";
P_HTM[10414]="*“Alaṃ, sāriputta.**“Let it be, Sāriputta,*";
P_HTM[10415]="*Mā te rucci bhedakānuvattakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ puna upasampadā.**don’t think of reordaining the monks who sided with the schism.*";
P_HTM[10416]="*Tena hi tvaṃ, sāriputta, bhedakānuvattake bhikkhū thullaccayaṃ desāpehi.**Instead, have them confess a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[10417]="*Kathaṃ pana te, sāriputta, devadatto paṭipajjī”ti?**And Devadatta, how did he treat you?”*";
P_HTM[10418]="*“Yatheva, bhante, bhagavā bahudeva rattiṃ bhikkhū dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā maṃ ajjhesati—**“Just as you, Sir, spend most of the night instructing, inspiring, and gladdening the monks with a teaching, and then invite me, saying,*";
P_HTM[10419]="*‘vigatathinamiddho kho, sāriputta, bhikkhusaṅgho;**‘The Sangha of monks is without dullness and drowsiness.*";
P_HTM[10420]="*paṭibhātu taṃ, sāriputta, bhikkhūnaṃ dhammī kathā, piṭṭhi me āgilāyati, tamahaṃ āyamissāmī’ti.**Give a teaching, Sāriputta. My back is aching and I’ll stretch it,’*";
P_HTM[10421]="*Evameva kho, bhante, devadatto paṭipajjī”ti.**that’s how Devadatta treated us.”*";
P_HTM[10422]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi—**And the Buddha addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[10423]="*“bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, araññāyatane mahāsarasī.**“Once upon a time there was a great lake in a wilderness area,*";
P_HTM[10424]="*Taṃ nāgā upanissāya vihariṃsu.**with elephants living nearby.*";
P_HTM[10425]="*Te taṃ sarasiṃ ogāhetvā, soṇḍāya bhisamuḷālaṃ abbuhitvā, suvikkhālitaṃ vikkhāletvā, akaddamaṃ saṅkhāditvā ajjhoharanti.**They plunged into the lake, pulled up lotus roots and tubers with their trunks, gave them a good rinse to remove the mud, and then chewed and swallowed them.*";
P_HTM[10426]="*Tesaṃ taṃ vaṇṇāya ceva hoti, balāya ca.**That gave them beauty and strength.*";
P_HTM[10427]="*Na ca tatonidānaṃ maraṇaṃ vā nigacchanti, maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhaṃ.**And they didn’t die or experience death-like suffering because of that.*";
P_HTM[10428]="*Tesaṃyeva kho pana, bhikkhave, mahānāgānaṃ anusikkhamānā taruṇā bhiṅkacchāpā.**Then baby elephants tried to imitate those great elephants.*";
P_HTM[10429]="*Te taṃ sarasiṃ ogāhetvā, soṇḍāya bhisamuḷālaṃ abbuhitvā, na suvikkhālitaṃ vikkhāletvā, sakaddamaṃ saṅkhāditvā, ajjhoharanti.**They plunged into the lake, pulled up lotus roots and tubers with their trunks, but didn’t give them a good rinse to remove the mud, and then chewed and swallowed them while muddy.*";
P_HTM[10430]="*Tesaṃ taṃ neva vaṇṇāya hoti, na balāya.**That didn’t give them any beauty or strength.*";
P_HTM[10431]="*Tatonidānañca maraṇaṃ vā nigacchanti, maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhaṃ.**And they died or experienced death-like suffering because of that.*";
P_HTM[10432]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, devadatto mamānukrubbaṃ kapaṇo marissatīti.**Just so, by imitating me, Devadatta will die miserably.*";
P_HTM[10433]="*Mahāvarāhassa mahiṃ vikrubbato,**‘While the great elephant removes the earth,*";
P_HTM[10434]="*Bhisaṃ ghasānassa nadīsu jaggato;**Eats the tuber, and is alert in the rivers,*";
P_HTM[10435]="*Bhiṅkova paṅkaṃ abhibhakkhayitvā,**He’s like a baby elephant that’s eaten mud:*";
P_HTM[10436]="*Mamānukrubbaṃ kapaṇo marissatīti.**By imitating me, he will die miserably.’*";
P_HTM[10437]="*Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu dūteyyaṃ gantumarahati.**A monk who has eight qualities is qualified to act as messenger.*";
P_HTM[10438]="*Katamehi aṭṭhahi?* **";
P_HTM[10439]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sotā ca hoti, sāvetā ca, uggahetā ca, dhāretā ca, viññātā ca, viññāpetā ca, kusalo ca sahitāsahitassa, no ca kalahakārako—**He listens and communicates, he learns and remembers, he understands and gets things across, he’s skilled in what is and what isn’t relevant, he’s not argumentative.*";
P_HTM[10440]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu dūteyyaṃ gantumarahati.* **";
P_HTM[10441]="*Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato sāriputto dūteyyaṃ gantumarahati.* **";
P_HTM[10442]="*Katamehi aṭṭhahi?* **";
P_HTM[10443]="*Idha, bhikkhave, sāriputto sotā ca hoti, sāvetā ca, uggahetā ca, dhāretā ca, viññātā ca, viññāpetā ca, kusalo ca sahitāsahitassa, no ca kalahakārako—* **";
P_HTM[10444]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgato sāriputto dūteyyaṃ gantumarahatīti.**Because he has these eight qualities, Sāriputta is qualified to act as messenger.*";
P_HTM[10445]="*Yo ve na byathati patvā,**‘He doesn’t tremble when faced with*";
P_HTM[10446]="*parisaṃ uggavādiniṃ;**A gathering of fierce debaters.*";
P_HTM[10447]="*Na ca hāpeti vacanaṃ,**He doesn’t mangle his words*";
P_HTM[10448]="*na ca chādeti sāsanaṃ.**Or fail to get the instruction across.*";
P_HTM[10449]="*Asandiddho ca akkhāti,**He speaks with confidence*";
P_HTM[10450]="*Pucchito ca na kuppati;**And isn’t agitated when questioned.*";
P_HTM[10451]="*Sa ve tādisako bhikkhu,**This kind of monk, indeed,*";
P_HTM[10452]="*Dūteyyaṃ gantumarahatīti.**Is qualified to act as messenger.’*";
P_HTM[10453]="*Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, asaddhammehi abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto devadatto āpāyiko nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho.**Because he is overcome by and immersed in eight bad qualities, Devadatta is irredeemably destined to an eon in hell.*";
P_HTM[10454]="*Katamehi aṭṭhahi?* **";
P_HTM[10455]="*Lābhena, bhikkhave, abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto devadatto āpāyiko nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho;**Because Devadatta is overcome by and immersed in gain,*";
P_HTM[10456]="*alābhena, bhikkhave …pe…**lack of gain,*";
P_HTM[10457]="*yasena, bhikkhave …pe…**fame,*";
P_HTM[10458]="*ayasena, bhikkhave …pe…**lack of fame,*";
P_HTM[10459]="*sakkārena, bhikkhave …pe…**honor,*";
P_HTM[10460]="*asakkārena, bhikkhave …pe…**lack of honor,*";
P_HTM[10461]="*pāpicchatāya, bhikkhave …pe…**bad desires,*";
P_HTM[10462]="*pāpamittatāya bhikkhave, abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto devadatto āpāyiko nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho—**and bad friends, he is irredeemably destined to an eon in hell.*";
P_HTM[10463]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahi asaddhammehi abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto devadatto āpāyiko nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho.* **";
P_HTM[10464]="*Sādhu, bhikkhave, bhikkhu uppannaṃ lābhaṃ abhibhuyya abhibhuyya vihareyya, uppannaṃ alābhaṃ …pe…**It’s good for a monk to overcome whatever gain he’s affected by, whatever lack of gain he’s affected by,*";
P_HTM[10465]="*uppannaṃ yasaṃ …**whatever fame he’s affected by,*";
P_HTM[10466]="*uppannaṃ ayasaṃ …**whatever lack of fame he’s affected by,*";
P_HTM[10467]="*uppannaṃ sakkāraṃ …**whatever honor he’s affected by,*";
P_HTM[10468]="*uppannaṃ asakkāraṃ …**whatever lack of honor he’s affected by,*";
P_HTM[10469]="*uppannaṃ pāpicchataṃ …**whatever bad desires he’s affected by,*";
P_HTM[10470]="*uppannaṃ pāpamittataṃ abhibhuyya abhibhuyya vihareyya.**or whatever bad friends he’s affected by.*";
P_HTM[10471]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthavasaṃ paṭicca uppannaṃ lābhaṃ abhibhuyya abhibhuyya vihareyya, uppannaṃ alābhaṃ …pe…**For what reason should a monk overcome these things?*";
P_HTM[10472]="*uppannaṃ yasaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[10473]="*uppannaṃ ayasaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[10474]="*uppannaṃ sakkāraṃ …* **";
P_HTM[10475]="*uppannaṃ asakkāraṃ …* **";
P_HTM[10476]="*uppannaṃ pāpicchataṃ …* **";
P_HTM[10477]="*uppannaṃ pāpamittataṃ abhibhuyya abhibhuyya vihareyya?* **";
P_HTM[10478]="*Yaṃ hissa, bhikkhave, uppannaṃ lābhaṃ anabhibhuyya viharato uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, uppannaṃ lābhaṃ abhibhuyya abhibhuyya viharato evaṃsate āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti.**If he doesn’t overcome whatever gain he’s affected by, corruptions, distress, and fevers may arise. But if he overcomes whatever gain he’s affected by, he won’t have those corruptions, distress, and fevers.*";
P_HTM[10479]="*Yaṃ hissa, bhikkhave, uppannaṃ alābhaṃ …pe…**If he doesn’t overcome whatever lack of gain he’s affected by,*";
P_HTM[10480]="*uppannaṃ yasaṃ …**whatever fame he’s affected by,*";
P_HTM[10481]="*uppannaṃ ayasaṃ …**whatever lack of fame he’s affected by,*";
P_HTM[10482]="*uppannaṃ sakkāraṃ …**whatever honor he’s affected by,*";
P_HTM[10483]="*uppannaṃ asakkāraṃ …**whatever lack of honor he’s affected by,*";
P_HTM[10484]="*uppannaṃ pāpicchataṃ …**whatever bad desires he’s affected by,*";
P_HTM[10485]="*uppannaṃ pāpamittataṃ anabhibhuyya viharato uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, uppannaṃ pāpamittataṃ abhibhuyya abhibhuyya viharato evaṃsate āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti.**or whatever bad friends he’s affected by, corruptions, distress, and fevers may arise. But if he overcomes whatever bad friends he’s affected by, he won’t have those corruptions, distress, and fevers.*";
P_HTM[10486]="*Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, atthavasaṃ paṭicca uppannaṃ lābhaṃ abhibhuyya abhibhuyya vihareyya, uppannaṃ alābhaṃ …pe…**Therefore, monks, you should overcome whatever gain you’re affected by, whatever lack of gain you’re affected by,*";
P_HTM[10487]="*uppannaṃ yasaṃ …**whatever fame you’re affected by,*";
P_HTM[10488]="*uppannaṃ ayasaṃ …**whatever lack of fame you’re affected by,*";
P_HTM[10489]="*uppannaṃ sakkāraṃ …**whatever honor you’re affected by,*";
P_HTM[10490]="*uppannaṃ asakkāraṃ …**whatever lack of honor you’re affected by,*";
P_HTM[10491]="*uppannaṃ pāpicchataṃ …**whatever bad desires you’re affected by,*";
P_HTM[10492]="*uppannaṃ pāpamittataṃ abhibhuyya abhibhuyya vihareyya.**and whatever bad friends you’re affected by.*";
P_HTM[10493]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, uppannaṃ lābhaṃ abhibhuyya abhibhuyya viharissāma, uppannaṃ alābhaṃ …pe…* **";
P_HTM[10494]="*uppannaṃ yasaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[10495]="*uppannaṃ ayasaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[10496]="*uppannaṃ sakkāraṃ …* **";
P_HTM[10497]="*uppannaṃ asakkāraṃ …* **";
P_HTM[10498]="*uppannaṃ pāpicchataṃ …* **";
P_HTM[10499]="*uppannaṃ pāpamittataṃ abhibhuyya abhibhuyya viharissāmāti;* **";
P_HTM[10500]="*evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbanti.**It’s in this way you should train yourselves.*";
P_HTM[10501]="*Tīhi, bhikkhave, asaddhammehi abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto devadatto āpāyiko nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekiccho.**Because he is overcome by and immersed in three bad qualities, Devadatta is irredeemably destined to an eon in hell.*";
P_HTM[10502]="*Katamehi tīhi?**What three?*";
P_HTM[10503]="*Pāpicchatā, pāpamittatā, oramattakena visesādhigamena antarā vosānaṃ āpādi—**Bad desires; bad friends; after minor success, he stopped short of the goal.*";
P_HTM[10504]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhi asaddhammehi abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto devadatto āpāyiko nerayiko kappaṭṭho atekicchoti.* **";
P_HTM[10505]="*Mā jātu koci lokasmiṃ,**‘No one with bad desires*";
P_HTM[10506]="*pāpiccho udapajjatha;**Is ever reborn in this world.*";
P_HTM[10507]="*Tadamināpi jānātha,**In this way you may know*";
P_HTM[10508]="*pāpicchānaṃ yathāgati.**The destination of those with bad desires.*";
P_HTM[10509]="*Paṇḍitoti samaññāto,**Designated as “wise”,*";
P_HTM[10510]="*bhāvitattoti sammato;**Agreed upon as “well-trained”,*";
P_HTM[10511]="*Jalaṃva yasasā aṭṭhā,**It was as if he was shining with fame—*";
P_HTM[10512]="*devadattoti me sutaṃ.**I have heard Devadatta was like this.*";
P_HTM[10513]="*So pamādaṃ anuciṇṇo,**He was heedless,*";
P_HTM[10514]="*āsajja naṃ tathāgataṃ;**And after hurting the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[10515]="*Avīcinirayaṃ patto,**He’s gone to the Avīci hell,*";
P_HTM[10516]="*catudvāraṃ bhayānakaṃ.**Frightful and with four doors.*";
P_HTM[10517]="*Aduṭṭhassa hi yo dubbhe,**If you hurt one free from anger,*";
P_HTM[10518]="*pāpakammaṃ akrubbato;**One who doesn’t do anything bad,*";
P_HTM[10519]="*Tameva pāpaṃ phusati,**You experience that evil yourself,*";
P_HTM[10520]="*duṭṭhacittaṃ anādaraṃ.**Being evil-minded and disrespectful.*";
P_HTM[10521]="*Samuddaṃ visakumbhena,**You might think to pollute*";
P_HTM[10522]="*yo maññeyya padūsituṃ;**The ocean with a pot of poison,*";
P_HTM[10523]="*Na so tena padūseyya,**But you would not be able to do so,*";
P_HTM[10524]="*bhesmā hi udadhī mahā.**For the ocean is frightfully large.*";
P_HTM[10525]="*Evameva tathāgataṃ,**It’s the same with the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[10526]="*yo vādenupahiṃsati;**If by speech one tries to harm him—*";
P_HTM[10527]="*Samaggataṃ santacittaṃ,**With his right conduct and peaceful mind—*";
P_HTM[10528]="*vādo tamhi na rūhati.**That speech doesn’t affect him.*";
P_HTM[10529]="*Tādisaṃ mittaṃ krubbetha,**The wise make friends with such a person,*";
P_HTM[10530]="*tañca sevetha paṇḍito;**And they associate with him.*";
P_HTM[10531]="*Yassa maggānugo bhikkhu,**The monk who follows his path,*";
P_HTM[10532]="*khayaṃ dukkhassa pāpuṇe”ti.**Achieves the end of suffering.’”*";
P_HTM[10533]="*2. Upālipañhā**3.2 Upāli’s questions*";
P_HTM[10534]="*Atha kho āyasmā upāli yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**On one occasion Upāli went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[10535]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā upāli bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[10536]="*“saṅgharāji saṅgharājīti, bhante, vuccati.**“Venerable Sir, we speak of ‘fracture in the Sangha’.*";
P_HTM[10537]="*Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, saṅgharāji hoti, no ca saṅghabhedo?**But how is there fracture in the Sangha, yet not schism in the Sangha?*";
P_HTM[10538]="*Kittāvatā ca pana saṅgharāji ceva hoti saṅghabhedo cā”ti?**And how is there both fracture  and schism in the Sangha?”*";
P_HTM[10539]="*“Ekato, upāli, eko hoti, ekato dve, catuttho anussāveti, salākaṃ gāheti—**“If, Upāli, there is one monk on one side and two on the other, and a fourth makes the proclamation and distributes voting tickets, saying,*";
P_HTM[10540]="*‘ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanaṃ, imaṃ gaṇhatha, imaṃ rocethā’ti.**‘This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction; take this, approve of this,’*";
P_HTM[10541]="*Evampi kho, upāli, saṅgharāji hoti, no ca saṅghabhedo.**then this is a fracture in the Sangha, but not schism in the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[10542]="*Ekato, upāli, dve honti, ekato dve, pañcamo anussāveti, salākaṃ gāheti—**If there are two monks on one side and two on the other, and a fifth makes the proclamation and distributes voting tickets, saying,*";
P_HTM[10543]="*‘ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanaṃ, imaṃ gaṇhatha, imaṃ rocethā’ti.**‘This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction; take this, approve of this,’*";
P_HTM[10544]="*Evampi kho, upāli, saṅgharāji hoti, no ca saṅghabhedo.**then this is a fracture in the Sangha, but not schism in the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[10545]="*Ekato, upāli, dve honti, ekato tayo, chaṭṭho anussāveti, salākaṃ gāheti—**If there are two monks on one side and three on the other, and a sixth makes the proclamation and distributes voting tickets, saying,*";
P_HTM[10546]="*‘ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanaṃ, imaṃ gaṇhatha, imaṃ rocethā’ti.**‘This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction; take this, approve of this,’*";
P_HTM[10547]="*Evampi kho, upāli, saṅgharāji hoti, no ca saṅghabhedo.**then this is a fracture in the Sangha, but not schism in the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[10548]="*Ekato, upāli, tayo honti, ekato tayo, sattamo anussāveti, salākaṃ gāheti—**If there are three monks on one side and three on the other, and a seventh makes the proclamation and distributes voting tickets, saying,*";
P_HTM[10549]="*‘ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanaṃ, imaṃ gaṇhatha, imaṃ rocethā’ti.**‘This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction; take this, approve of this,’*";
P_HTM[10550]="*Evampi kho, upāli, saṅgharāji hoti, no ca saṅghabhedo.**then this is a fracture in the Sangha, but not schism in the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[10551]="*Ekato, upāli, tayo honti, ekato cattāro, aṭṭhamo anussāveti, salākaṃ gāheti—**If there are three monks on one side and four on the other, and an eighth makes the proclamation and distributes voting tickets, saying,*";
P_HTM[10552]="*‘ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanaṃ, imaṃ gaṇhatha, imaṃ rocethā’ti.**‘This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction; take this, approve of this,’*";
P_HTM[10553]="*Evampi kho, upāli, saṅgharāji hoti, no ca saṅghabhedo.**then this is a fracture in the Sangha, but not schism in the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[10554]="*Ekato, upāli, cattāro honti, ekato cattāro, navamo anussāveti, salākaṃ gāheti—**But if there are four monks on one side and four on the other, and a ninth makes the proclamation and distributes voting tickets, saying,*";
P_HTM[10555]="*‘ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanaṃ, imaṃ gaṇhatha, imaṃ rocethā’ti.**‘This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction; take this, approve of this,’*";
P_HTM[10556]="*Evaṃ kho, upāli, saṅgharāji ceva hoti saṅghabhedo ca.**then this is both a fracture in the Sangha and also a schism in the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[10557]="*Navannaṃ vā, upāli, atirekanavannaṃ vā saṅgharāji ceva hoti saṅghabhedo ca.**And if there are nine or more monks, then this is both a fracture in the Sangha and also a schism in the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[10558]="*Na kho, upāli, bhikkhunī saṅghaṃ bhindati, api ca bhedāya parakkamati, na sikkhamānā saṅghaṃ bhindati …pe…**A nun cannot cause a schism in the Sangha, even if she makes an effort to cause a schism. A trainee nun,*";
P_HTM[10559]="*na sāmaṇero saṅghaṃ bhindati, na sāmaṇerī saṅghaṃ bhindati, na upāsako saṅghaṃ bhindati, na upāsikā saṅghaṃ bhindati, api ca bhedāya parakkamati.**a novice monk, a novice nun, a male lay follower, or a female lay follower cannot cause a schism in the Sangha, even if she makes an effort to cause a schism.*";
P_HTM[10560]="*Bhikkhu kho, upāli, pakatatto, samānasaṃvāsako, samānasīmāyaṃ ṭhito, saṅghaṃ bhindatī”ti.**Only a monk of regular standing, one who belongs to the same Buddhist sect and is present within the same monastic boundary, can cause a schism in the Sangha.”*";
P_HTM[10561]="*“Saṅghabhedo saṅghabhedoti, bhante, vuccati.**“Venerable Sir, we speak of ‘schism in the Sangha’.*";
P_HTM[10562]="*Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, saṅgho bhinno hotī”ti?**But how is there schism in the Sangha?”*";
P_HTM[10563]="*“Idhupāli, bhikkhū adhammaṃ dhammoti dīpenti.**“Take the case when monks proclaim what is contrary to the Teaching as the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[10564]="*Dhammaṃ adhammoti dīpenti.**They proclaim what is the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[10565]="*Avinayaṃ vinayoti dīpenti.**They proclaim what is contrary to the Monastic Law as the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[10566]="*Vinayaṃ avinayoti dīpenti.**They proclaim what is the Monastic Law as contrary to the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[10567]="*Abhāsitaṃ alapitaṃ tathāgatena bhāsitaṃ lapitaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpenti.**They proclaim what hasn’t been spoken by the Buddha as spoken by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[10568]="*Bhāsitaṃ lapitaṃ tathāgatena abhāsitaṃ alapitaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpenti.**They proclaim what has been spoken by the Buddha as not spoken by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[10569]="*Anāciṇṇaṃ tathāgatena āciṇṇaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpenti.**They proclaim what was not practiced by the Buddha as practiced by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[10570]="*Āciṇṇaṃ tathāgatena anāciṇṇaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpenti.**They proclaim what was practiced by the Buddha as not practiced by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[10571]="*Apaññattaṃ tathāgatena paññattaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpenti.**They proclaim what was not laid down by the Buddha as laid down by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[10572]="*Paññattaṃ tathāgatena apaññattaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpenti.**They proclaim what was laid down by the Buddha as not laid down by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[10573]="*Anāpattiṃ āpattīti dīpenti.**They proclaim a non-offense as an offense.*";
P_HTM[10574]="*Āpattiṃ anāpattīti dīpenti.**They proclaim an offense as a non-offense.*";
P_HTM[10575]="*Lahukaṃ āpattiṃ garukā āpattīti dīpenti.**They proclaim a light offense as heavy.*";
P_HTM[10576]="*Garukaṃ āpattiṃ lahukā āpattīti dīpenti.**They proclaim a heavy offense as light.*";
P_HTM[10577]="*Sāvasesaṃ āpattiṃ anavasesā āpattīti dīpenti.**They proclaim a curable offense as incurable.*";
P_HTM[10578]="*Anavasesaṃ āpattiṃ sāvasesā āpattīti dīpenti.**They proclaim an incurable offense as curable.*";
P_HTM[10579]="*Duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ aduṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpenti.**They proclaim a grave offense as minor.*";
P_HTM[10580]="*Aduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ duṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpenti.**They proclaim a minor offense as grave.*";
P_HTM[10581]="*Te imehi aṭṭhārasahi vatthūhi apakassanti, avapakassanti, āveniṃ uposathaṃ karonti, āveniṃ pavāraṇaṃ karonti, āveniṃ saṅghakammaṃ karonti.**If, based on any of these eighteen grounds, they pull away and separate, and they do the observance-day procedure, the invitation procedure, or legal procedures of the Sangha separately, then there is a schism in the Sangha.”*";
P_HTM[10582]="*Ettāvatā kho, upāli, saṅgho bhinno hotī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10583]="*“Saṅghasāmaggī saṅghasāmaggīti, bhante, vuccati.**“Venerable Sir, we speak of ‘unity in the Sangha’.*";
P_HTM[10584]="*Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, saṅgho samaggo hotī”ti?**But how is there unity in the Sangha?”*";
P_HTM[10585]="*“Idhupāli, bhikkhū adhammaṃ adhammoti dīpenti.**“Take the case when monks proclaim what is contrary to the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[10586]="*Dhammaṃ dhammoti dīpenti.**They proclaim what is the Teaching as the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[10587]="*Avinayaṃ avinayoti dīpenti.**They proclaim what is contrary to the Monastic Law as contrary to the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[10588]="*Vinayaṃ vinayoti dīpenti.**They proclaim what is the Monastic Law as the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[10589]="*Abhāsitaṃ alapitaṃ tathāgatena abhāsitaṃ alapitaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpenti.**They proclaim what hasn’t been spoken by the Buddha as not spoken by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[10590]="*Bhāsitaṃ lapitaṃ tathāgatena bhāsitaṃ lapitaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpenti.**They proclaim what has been spoken by the Buddha as spoken by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[10591]="*Anāciṇṇaṃ tathāgatena anāciṇṇaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpenti.**They proclaim what was not practiced by the Buddha as not practiced by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[10592]="*Āciṇṇaṃ tathāgatena āciṇṇaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpenti.**They proclaim what was practiced by the Buddha as practiced by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[10593]="*Apaññattaṃ tathāgatena apaññattaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpenti.**They proclaim what was not laid down by the Buddha as not laid down by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[10594]="*Paññattaṃ tathāgatena paññattaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpenti.**They proclaim what was laid down by the Buddha as laid down by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[10595]="*Anāpattiṃ anāpattīti dīpenti.**They proclaim a non-offense as a non-offense.*";
P_HTM[10596]="*Āpattiṃ āpattīti dīpenti.**They proclaim an offense as an offense.*";
P_HTM[10597]="*Lahukaṃ āpattiṃ lahukā āpattīti dīpenti.**They proclaim a light offense as light.*";
P_HTM[10598]="*Garukaṃ āpattiṃ garukā āpattīti dīpenti.**They proclaim a heavy offense as heavy.*";
P_HTM[10599]="*Sāvasesaṃ āpattiṃ sāvasesā āpattīti dīpenti.**They proclaim a curable offense as curable.*";
P_HTM[10600]="*Anavasesaṃ āpattiṃ anavasesā āpattīti dīpenti.**They proclaim an incurable offense as incurable.*";
P_HTM[10601]="*Duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ duṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpenti.**They proclaim a grave offense as grave.*";
P_HTM[10602]="*Aduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ aduṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpenti.**They proclaim a minor offense as minor.*";
P_HTM[10603]="*Te imehi aṭṭhārasahi vatthūhi na apakassanti, na avapakassanti, na āveniṃ uposathaṃ karonti, na āveniṃ pavāraṇaṃ karonti, na āveniṃ saṅghakammaṃ karonti.**If, based on any of these eighteen grounds, they don’t pull away or separate, and they don’t do the observance-day procedure, the invitation procedure, or legal procedures of the Sangha separately,*";
P_HTM[10604]="*Ettāvatā kho, upāli, saṅgho samaggo hotī”ti.**then there is unity in the Sangha.”*";
P_HTM[10605]="*“Samaggaṃ pana, bhante, saṅghaṃ bhinditvā kiṃ so pasavatī”ti?**“But, Sir, what is the consequence of causing a schism in a united Sangha?”*";
P_HTM[10606]="*“Samaggaṃ kho, upāli, saṅghaṃ bhinditvā kappaṭṭhikaṃ kibbisaṃ pasavati, kappaṃ nirayamhi paccatīti.**“Anyone who causes a schism in a united Sangha does a bad act with effect for an eon; he’s boiled in hell for an eon.*";
P_HTM[10607]="*Āpāyiko nerayiko,**‘Going downwards, bound for hell—*";
P_HTM[10608]="*Kappaṭṭho saṅghabhedako;**The schismatic stays there for an eon.*";
P_HTM[10609]="*Vaggarato adhammaṭṭho,**Delighting in division and immoral,*";
P_HTM[10610]="*Yogakkhemā padhaṃsati;**Barred from sanctuary,*";
P_HTM[10611]="*Saṅghaṃ samaggaṃ bhinditvā,**Having divided a united Sangha,*";
P_HTM[10612]="*Kappaṃ nirayamhi paccatī”ti.**He boils in hell for an eon.’”*";
P_HTM[10613]="*“Bhinnaṃ pana, bhante, saṅghaṃ samaggaṃ katvā kiṃ so pasavatī”ti?**“But, Sir, what is the consequence of uniting a schismatic sangha?”*";
P_HTM[10614]="*“Bhinnaṃ kho, upāli, saṅghaṃ samaggaṃ katvā brahmaṃ puññaṃ pasavati, kappaṃ saggamhi modatīti.**“Anyone who unites a schismatic sangha generates supreme merit; he rejoices in heaven for an eon.*";
P_HTM[10615]="*Sukhā saṅghassa sāmaggī,**‘Pleasant is unity in the Sangha,*";
P_HTM[10616]="*samaggānañca anuggaho;**And to help in fostering harmony.*";
P_HTM[10617]="*Samaggarato dhammaṭṭho,**Delighting in unity and moral,*";
P_HTM[10618]="*yogakkhemā na dhaṃsati;**Not barred from sanctuary,*";
P_HTM[10619]="*Saṅghaṃ samaggaṃ katvāna,**Having united the Sangha,*";
P_HTM[10620]="*kappaṃ saggamhi modatī”ti.**He rejoices in heaven for an eon.’”*";
P_HTM[10621]="*“Siyā nu kho, bhante, saṅghabhedako āpāyiko, nerayiko, kappaṭṭho, atekiccho”ti?**“Might one who causes a schism in the Sangha be irredeemably destined to an eon in hell?”*";
P_HTM[10622]="*“Siyā, upāli, saṅghabhedako āpāyiko, nerayiko, kappaṭṭho, atekiccho”ti.**“He might.”*";
P_HTM[10623]="*“Siyā pana, bhante, saṅghabhedako na āpāyiko, na nerayiko, na kappaṭṭho, na atekiccho”ti?**“Might one who causes a schism in the Sangha not be irredeemably destined to an eon in hell?”*";
P_HTM[10624]="*“Siyā, upāli, saṅghabhedako na āpāyiko, na nerayiko, na kappaṭṭho, na atekiccho”ti.**“He might.”*";
P_HTM[10625]="*“Katamo pana, bhante, saṅghabhedako āpāyiko, nerayiko, kappaṭṭho, atekiccho”ti?**“What sort of person who causes a schism in the Sangha is irredeemably destined to an eon in hell?”*";
P_HTM[10626]="*“Idhupāli, bhikkhu adhammaṃ dhammoti dīpeti.**“In this case a monk proclaims what is contrary to the Teaching as the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[10627]="*Tasmiṃ adhammadiṭṭhi, bhede adhammadiṭṭhi, vinidhāya diṭṭhiṃ, vinidhāya khantiṃ, vinidhāya ruciṃ, vinidhāya bhāvaṃ, anussāveti, salākaṃ gāheti—**He has the view that what he says is illegitimate and the view that the schism is illegitimate. He misrepresents his view of what is true, his belief of what is true, his acceptance of what is true, and his sentiment of what is true. He makes a proclamation and distributes voting tickets, saying,*";
P_HTM[10628]="*‘ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanaṃ, imaṃ gaṇhatha, imaṃ rocethā’ti.**‘This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction; take this, approve of this.’*";
P_HTM[10629]="*Ayampi kho, upāli, saṅghabhedako āpāyiko, nerayiko, kappaṭṭho, atekiccho.**This person who causes a schism in the Sangha is irredeemably destined to an eon in hell.*";
P_HTM[10630]="*Puna caparaṃ, upāli, bhikkhu adhammaṃ dhammoti dīpeti.**Again, a monk proclaims what is contrary to the Teaching as the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[10631]="*Tasmiṃ adhammadiṭṭhi, bhede dhammadiṭṭhi, vinidhāya diṭṭhiṃ, vinidhāya khantiṃ, vinidhāya ruciṃ, vinidhāya bhāvaṃ, anussāveti, salākaṃ gāheti—**He has the view that what he says is illegitimate, but the view that the schism is legitimate. He misrepresents his view of what is true, his belief of what is true, his acceptance of what is true, and his sentiment of what is true. He makes a proclamation and distributes voting tickets, saying,*";
P_HTM[10632]="*‘ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanaṃ, imaṃ gaṇhatha, imaṃ rocethā’ti.**‘This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction; take this, approve of this.’*";
P_HTM[10633]="*Ayampi kho, upāli, saṅghabhedako āpāyiko, nerayiko, kappaṭṭho, atekiccho.**This person, too, who causes a schism in the Sangha is irredeemably destined to an eon in hell.*";
P_HTM[10634]="*Puna caparaṃ, upāli, bhikkhu adhammaṃ dhammoti dīpeti.**Again, a monk proclaims what is contrary to the Teaching as the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[10635]="*Tasmiṃ adhammadiṭṭhi, bhede vematiko, vinidhāya diṭṭhiṃ, vinidhāya khantiṃ, vinidhāya ruciṃ, vinidhāya bhāvaṃ, anussāveti, salākaṃ gāheti—**He has the view that what he says is illegitimate, but is unsure about the schism. He misrepresents his view of what is true, his belief of what is true, his acceptance of what is true, and his sentiment of what is true. He makes a proclamation and distributes voting tickets, saying,*";
P_HTM[10636]="*‘ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanaṃ, imaṃ gaṇhatha, imaṃ rocethā’ti.**‘This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction; take this, approve of this.’*";
P_HTM[10637]="*Ayampi kho, upāli, saṅghabhedako āpāyiko, nerayiko, kappaṭṭho, atekiccho.**This person, too, who causes a schism in the Sangha is irredeemably destined to an eon in hell.*";
P_HTM[10638]="*Puna caparaṃ, upāli, bhikkhu adhammaṃ dhammoti dīpeti.**Again, a monk proclaims what is contrary to the Teaching as the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[10639]="*Tasmiṃ dhammadiṭṭhi, bhede adhammadiṭṭhi …pe…**He has the view that what he says is legitimate, but the view that the schism is illegitimate …*";
P_HTM[10640]="*tasmiṃ dhammadiṭṭhi bhede dhammadiṭṭhi.* **";
P_HTM[10641]="*Tasmiṃ dhammadiṭṭhi bhede vematiko.**He has the view that what he says is legitimate, but is unsure about the schism …*";
P_HTM[10642]="*Tasmiṃ vematiko bhede adhammadiṭṭhi.**He is unsure about what he says, but has the view that the schism is illegitimate …*";
P_HTM[10643]="*Tasmiṃ vematiko bhede dhammadiṭṭhi.**He is unsure about what he says, but has the view that the schism is legitimate …*";
P_HTM[10644]="*Tasmiṃ vematiko bhede vematiko vinidhāya diṭṭhiṃ, vinidhāya khantiṃ, vinidhāya ruciṃ, vinidhāya bhāvaṃ, anussāveti, salākaṃ gāheti—**He is unsure about what he says and is unsure about the schism. He misrepresents his view of what is true, his belief of what is true, his acceptance of what is true, and his sentiment of what is true. He makes a proclamation and distributes voting tickets, saying,*";
P_HTM[10645]="*‘ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanaṃ, imaṃ gaṇhatha, imaṃ rocethā’ti.**‘This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction; take this, approve of this.’*";
P_HTM[10646]="*Ayampi kho, upāli, saṅghabhedako āpāyiko, nerayiko, kappaṭṭho, atekiccho.**This person, too, who causes a schism in the Sangha is irredeemably destined to an eon in hell.*";
P_HTM[10647]="*Puna caparaṃ, upāli, bhikkhu dhammaṃ adhammoti dīpeti …pe…**Again, a monk proclaims what is the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching,*";
P_HTM[10648]="*avinayaṃ vinayoti dīpeti …**what is contrary to the Monastic Law as the Monastic Law,*";
P_HTM[10649]="*vinayaṃ avinayoti dīpeti …**what is the Monastic Law as contrary to the Monastic Law,*";
P_HTM[10650]="*abhāsitaṃ alapitaṃ tathāgatena bhāsitaṃ lapitaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpeti …**what hasn’t been spoken by the Buddha as spoken by the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[10651]="*bhāsitaṃ lapitaṃ tathāgatena abhāsitaṃ alapitaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpeti …**what has been spoken by the Buddha as not spoken by the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[10652]="*anāciṇṇaṃ tathāgatena āciṇṇaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpeti …**what was not practiced by the Buddha as practiced by the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[10653]="*āciṇṇaṃ tathāgatena anāciṇṇaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpeti …**what was practiced by the Buddha as not practiced by the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[10654]="*apaññattaṃ tathāgatena paññattaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpeti …**what was not laid down by the Buddha as laid down by the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[10655]="*paññattaṃ tathāgatena apaññattaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpeti …**what was laid down by the Buddha as not laid down by the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[10656]="*anāpattiṃ āpattīti dīpeti …**a non-offense as an offense,*";
P_HTM[10657]="*āpattiṃ anāpattīti dīpeti …**an offense as a non-offense,*";
P_HTM[10658]="*lahukaṃ āpattiṃ garukā āpattīti dīpeti …**a light offense as heavy,*";
P_HTM[10659]="*garukaṃ āpattiṃ lahukā āpattīti dīpeti …**a heavy offense as light,*";
P_HTM[10660]="*sāvasesaṃ āpattiṃ anavasesā āpattīti dīpeti …**a curable offense as incurable,*";
P_HTM[10661]="*anavasesaṃ āpattiṃ sāvasesā āpattīti dīpeti …**an incurable offense as curable,*";
P_HTM[10662]="*duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ aduṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpeti …**a grave offense as minor,*";
P_HTM[10663]="*aduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ duṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpeti …**or a minor offense as grave.*";
P_HTM[10664]="*tasmiṃ adhammadiṭṭhi, bhede adhammadiṭṭhi …pe…**He has the view that what he says is illegitimate and the view that the schism is illegitimate. …*";
P_HTM[10665]="*tasmiṃ adhammadiṭṭhi, bhede dhammadiṭṭhi …**He has the view that what he says is illegitimate, but the view that the schism is legitimate. …*";
P_HTM[10666]="*tasmiṃ adhammadiṭṭhi, bhede vematiko …**He has the view that what he says is illegitimate, but is unsure about the schism. …*";
P_HTM[10667]="*tasmiṃ dhammadiṭṭhi, bhede adhammadiṭṭhi …**He has the view that what he says is legitimate, but the view that the schism is illegitimate … …*";
P_HTM[10668]="*tasmiṃ dhammadiṭṭhi, bhede dhammadiṭṭhi …* **";
P_HTM[10669]="*tasmiṃ dhammadiṭṭhi, bhede vematiko …**He has the view that what he says is legitimate, but is unsure about the schism …*";
P_HTM[10670]="*tasmiṃ vematiko, bhede adhammadiṭṭhi …**He is unsure about what he says, but has the view that the schism is illegitimate …*";
P_HTM[10671]="*tasmiṃ vematiko, bhede dhammadiṭṭhi …**He is unsure about what he says, but has the view that the schism is legitimate …*";
P_HTM[10672]="*tasmiṃ vematiko, bhede vematiko, vinidhāya diṭṭhiṃ, vinidhāya khantiṃ, vinidhāya ruciṃ, vinidhāya bhāvaṃ, anussāveti, salākaṃ gāheti—**He is unsure about what he says and unsure about the schism. He misrepresents his view of what is true, his belief of what is true, his acceptance of what is true, and his sentiment of what is true. He makes a proclamation and distributes voting tickets, saying,*";
P_HTM[10673]="*‘ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanaṃ, imaṃ gaṇhatha, imaṃ rocethā’ti.**This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction; take this, approve of this.’*";
P_HTM[10674]="*Ayampi kho, upāli, saṅghabhedako āpāyiko, nerayiko, kappaṭṭho, atekiccho”ti.**This person, too, who causes a schism in the Sangha is irredeemably destined to an eon in hell.”*";
P_HTM[10675]="*“Katamo pana, bhante, saṅghabhedako na āpāyiko, na nerayiko, na kappaṭṭho, na atekiccho”ti?**“What sort of person who causes a schism in the Sangha isn’t irredeemably destined to an eon in hell?”*";
P_HTM[10676]="*“Idhupāli, bhikkhu adhammaṃ dhammoti dīpeti.**“In this case a monk proclaims what is contrary to the Teaching as the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[10677]="*Tasmiṃ dhammadiṭṭhi, bhede dhammadiṭṭhi, avinidhāya diṭṭhiṃ, avinidhāya khantiṃ, avinidhāya ruciṃ, avinidhāya bhāvaṃ, anussāveti, salākaṃ gāheti—**He has the view that what he says is legitimate and the view that the schism is legitimate. He doesn’t misrepresent his view of what is true, his belief of what is true, his acceptance of what is true, and his sentiment of what is true. He makes a proclamation and distributes voting tickets, saying,*";
P_HTM[10678]="*‘ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanaṃ, imaṃ gaṇhatha, imaṃ rocethā’ti.**‘This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction; take this, approve of this.’*";
P_HTM[10679]="*Ayampi kho, upāli, saṅghabhedako na āpāyiko, na nerayiko, na kappaṭṭho, na atekiccho.**This person who causes a schism in the Sangha isn’t irredeemably destined to an eon in hell.*";
P_HTM[10680]="*Puna caparaṃ, upāli, bhikkhu dhammaṃ adhammoti dīpeti …pe…**Again, a monk proclaims what is the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching …*";
P_HTM[10681]="*duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ aduṭṭhullā āpattīti dīpeti.**or a minor offense as grave.*";
P_HTM[10682]="*Tasmiṃ dhammadiṭṭhi, bhede dhammadiṭṭhi, avinidhāya diṭṭhiṃ, avinidhāya khantiṃ, avinidhāya ruciṃ, avinidhāya bhāvaṃ, anussāveti, salākaṃ gāheti—**He has the view that what he says is legitimate and the view that the schism is legitimate. He doesn’t misrepresent his view of what is true, his belief of what is true, his acceptance of what is true, and his sentiment of what is true. He makes a proclamation and distributes voting tickets, saying,*";
P_HTM[10683]="*‘ayaṃ dhammo, ayaṃ vinayo, idaṃ satthusāsanaṃ, imaṃ gaṇhatha, imaṃ rocethā’ti.**‘This is the Teaching, this is the Monastic Law, this is the Teacher’s instruction; take this, approve of this.’*";
P_HTM[10684]="*Ayampi kho, upāli, saṅghabhedako na āpāyiko, na nerayiko, na kappaṭṭho, na atekiccho”ti.**This person, too, who causes a schism in the Sangha isn’t irredeemably destined to an eon in hell.”*";
P_HTM[10685]="*Tatiyabhāṇavāro niṭṭhito.**The third section for recitation is finished.*";
P_HTM[10686]="*Saṅghabhedakakkhandhako sattamo.**The seventh chapter on schism in the Sangha is finished.*";
P_HTM[10687]="*Tassuddānaṃ* **";
P_HTM[10688]="*Anupiye abhiññātā,* **";
P_HTM[10689]="*sukhumālo na icchati;* **";
P_HTM[10690]="*Kasā vapā abhi ninne,* **";
P_HTM[10691]="*niddhā lāve ca ubbahe.* **";
P_HTM[10692]="*Puñjamaddapalālañca,* **";
P_HTM[10693]="*bhusaophuṇanīhare;* **";
P_HTM[10694]="*Āyatimpi na khīyanti,* **";
P_HTM[10695]="*pitaro ca pitāmahā.* **";
P_HTM[10696]="*Bhaddiyo anuruddho ca,* **";
P_HTM[10697]="*ānando bhagu kimilo;* **";
P_HTM[10698]="*Sakyamāno ca kosambiṃ,* **";
P_HTM[10699]="*parihāyi kakudhena ca.* **";
P_HTM[10700]="*Pakāsesi pituno ca,* **";
P_HTM[10701]="*purise silaṃ nāḷāgiriṃ;* **";
P_HTM[10702]="*Tikapañcagaruko kho,* **";
P_HTM[10703]="*bhindi thullaccayena ca;* **";
P_HTM[10704]="*Tayo aṭṭha puna tīṇi,* **";
P_HTM[10705]="*rāji bhedā siyā nu khoti.* **";
P_HTM[10706]="*Saṅghabhedakakkhandhako niṭṭhito.**The chapter on schism in the Sangha is finished.*";
P_HTM[10707]="*8. Vattakkhandhaka **8.  The chapter on proper conduct *";
P_HTM[10708]="*1. Āgantukavattakathā**1. Discussion of the proper conduct for newly arrived monks*";
P_HTM[10709]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[10710]="*Tena kho pana samayena āgantukā bhikkhū saupāhanāpi ārāmaṃ pavisanti, chattappaggahitāpi ārāmaṃ pavisanti, oguṇṭhitāpi ārāmaṃ pavisanti, sīsepi cīvaraṃ karitvā ārāmaṃ pavisanti, pānīyenapi pāde dhovanti, vuḍḍhatarepi āvāsike bhikkhū na abhivādenti, napi senāsanaṃ pucchanti.**At that time newly arrived monks entered the monastery wearing sandals, holding sunshades, with their heads covered, with their robes on their heads; and they washed their feet with drinking water, did not bow down to the more senior resident monks, and did not ask about dwellings.*";
P_HTM[10711]="*Aññataropi āgantuko bhikkhu anajjhāvuṭṭhaṃ vihāraṃ ghaṭikaṃ ugghāṭetvā kavāṭaṃ paṇāmetvā sahasā pāvisi.**A certain newly arrived monk unlocked the bolt of an unoccupied dwelling, opened the door, and entered hastily.*";
P_HTM[10712]="*Tassa uparipiṭṭhito ahi khandhe papati.**A snake fell from the top of the door frame onto his shoulders.*";
P_HTM[10713]="*So bhīto vissaramakāsi.**Terrified, he screamed.*";
P_HTM[10714]="*Bhikkhū upadhāvitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocuṃ—**The monks came running to*";
P_HTM[10715]="*“kissa tvaṃ, āvuso, vissaramakāsī”ti?**and asked why he was screaming.*";
P_HTM[10716]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**And he told them.*";
P_HTM[10717]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10718]="*“kathañhi nāma āgantukā bhikkhū saupāhanāpi ārāmaṃ pavisissanti, chattappaggahitāpi ārāmaṃ pavisissanti, oguṇṭhitāpi ārāmaṃ pavisissanti, sīsepi cīvaraṃ karitvā ārāmaṃ pavisissanti, pānīyenapi pāde dhovissanti, vuḍḍhatarepi āvāsike bhikkhū na abhivādessanti, napi senāsanaṃ pucchissantī”ti.**“How can the newly arrived monks enter the monastery wearing sandals, holding sunshades, with their heads covered, with their robe on their head; and wash their feet with drinking water, not bow down to the more senior resident monks, and not ask about dwellings?”*";
P_HTM[10719]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[10720]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, āgantukā bhikkhū saupāhanāpi ārāmaṃ pavisanti, chattappaggahitāpi ārāmaṃ pavisanti, oguṇṭhitāpi ārāmaṃ pavisanti, sīsepi cīvaraṃ karitvā ārāmaṃ pavisanti, pānīyenapi pāde dhovanti, vuḍḍhatarepi āvāsike bhikkhū na abhivādenti, napi senāsanaṃ pucchantī”ti.**“Is it true, monks, that the newly arrived monks act like this?”*";
P_HTM[10721]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10722]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[10723]="*kathañhi nāma bhikkhave āgantukā bhikkhū saupāhanāpi ārāmaṃ pavisissanti, chattappaggahitāpi ārāmaṃ pavisissanti, oguṇṭhitāpi ārāmaṃ pavisissanti, sīsepi cīvaraṃ karitvā ārāmaṃ pavisissanti, pānīyenapi pāde dhovissanti, vuḍḍhatarepi āvāsike bhikkhū na abhivādessanti, napi senāsanaṃ pucchissanti, netaṃ bhikkhave appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**“How can the newly arrived monks act like this? This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[10724]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[10725]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[10726]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, āgantukānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ vattaṃ paññapessāmi yathā āgantukehi bhikkhūhi sammā vattitabbaṃ.**“Well then, I will lay down the proper conduct for newly arrived monks.*";
P_HTM[10727]="*Āgantukena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā ‘idāni ārāmaṃ pavisissāmī’ti upāhanā omuñcitvā nīcaṃ katvā papphoṭetvā gahetvā chattaṃ apanāmetvā sīsaṃ vivaritvā sīse cīvaraṃ khandhe katvā sādhukaṃ ataramānena ārāmo pavisitabbo.**When a newly arrived monk enters a monastery, he should remove his sandals, hold them low, knock them together, and carry them along; he should lower his sunshade, uncover his head, and put his robe over his shoulders; he should then enter the monastery carefully and without hurry.*";
P_HTM[10728]="*Ārāmaṃ pavisantena sallakkhetabbaṃ—**As he enters the monastery,*";
P_HTM[10729]="*‘kattha āvāsikā bhikkhū paṭikkamantī’ti?**he should look out for where the resident monks gather—*";
P_HTM[10730]="*Yattha āvāsikā bhikkhū paṭikkamanti—* **";
P_HTM[10731]="*upaṭṭhānasālāya vā maṇḍape vā rukkhamūle vā—**whether it’s in the assembly hall, under a roof-cover, or at the foot of a tree—*";
P_HTM[10732]="*tattha gantvā ekamantaṃ patto nikkhipitabbo;**and he should go there.*";
P_HTM[10733]="*ekamantaṃ cīvaraṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ;**He should then put his bowl and robe aside,*";
P_HTM[10734]="*patirūpaṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā nisīditabbaṃ;**and sit down on a suitable seat.*";
P_HTM[10735]="*pānīyaṃ pucchitabbaṃ, paribhojanīyaṃ pucchitabbaṃ—**He should ask*";
P_HTM[10736]="*‘katamaṃ pānīyaṃ, katamaṃ paribhojanīyan’ti?**which is the water for drinking and which the water for washing.*";
P_HTM[10737]="*Sace pānīyena attho hoti, pānīyaṃ gahetvā pātabbaṃ.**If he needs water to drink, he may take some and drink.*";
P_HTM[10738]="*Sace paribhojanīyena attho hoti, paribhojanīyaṃ gahetvā pādā dhovitabbā.**If he needs water to wash, he may take some and wash his feet.*";
P_HTM[10739]="*Pāde dhovantena ekena hatthena udakaṃ āsiñcitabbaṃ, ekena hatthena pādā dhovitabbā.**When he washes his feet, he should pour the water with one hand and wash with the other.*";
P_HTM[10740]="*Na teneva udakaṃ āsiñcitabbaṃ na teneva hatthena pādā dhovitabbā.**He should not pour the water and wash his feet with the same hand.*";
P_HTM[10741]="*Upāhanāpuñchanacoḷakaṃ pucchitvā upāhanā puñchitabbā.**He should ask for a sandal-wiping cloth, and then wipe them.*";
P_HTM[10742]="*Upāhanā puñchantena paṭhamaṃ sukkhena coḷakena puñchitabbā, pacchā allena.**When he wipes his sandals, he should first wipe them with a dry cloth, then a wet one.*";
P_HTM[10743]="*Upāhanāpuñchanacoḷakaṃ dhovitvā ekamantaṃ vissajjetabbaṃ.**He should wash the cloth and put it aside.*";
P_HTM[10744]="*Sace āvāsiko bhikkhu vuḍḍho hoti, abhivādetabbo.**If a resident monk is more senior, the newly arrived monk should bow down to him.*";
P_HTM[10745]="*Sace navako hoti, abhivādāpetabbo.**If a resident monk is more junior, he should bow down to the newly arrived monk.*";
P_HTM[10746]="*Senāsanaṃ pucchitabbaṃ—‘katamaṃ me senāsanaṃ pāpuṇātī’ti?**The newly arrived monk should ask which dwelling he may use*";
P_HTM[10747]="*Ajjhāvuṭṭhaṃ vā anajjhāvuṭṭhaṃ vā pucchitabbaṃ, gocaro pucchitabbo, agocaro pucchitabbo, sekkhasammatāni kulāni pucchitabbāni, vaccaṭṭhānaṃ pucchitabbaṃ, passāvaṭṭhānaṃ pucchitabbaṃ, pānīyaṃ pucchitabbaṃ, paribhojanīyaṃ pucchitabbaṃ, kattaradaṇḍo pucchitabbo, saṅghassa katikasaṇṭhānaṃ pucchitabbaṃ—**and whether it’s occupied or not. He should ask about where to go for alms and where to avoid, about any families designated as “in training”, about the place for defecating and the place for urinating, about the water for drinking and the water for washing, about walking sticks, and about the Sangha’s agreements*";
P_HTM[10748]="*‘kaṃ kālaṃ pavisitabbaṃ, kaṃ kālaṃ nikkhamitabban’ti?**concerning the right time to enter and the right time to leave.*";
P_HTM[10749]="*Sace vihāro anajjhāvuttho hoti, kavāṭaṃ ākoṭetvā muhuttaṃ āgametvā ghaṭikaṃ ugghāṭetvā kavāṭaṃ paṇāmetvā bahi ṭhitena nilloketabbo.**If the dwelling is unoccupied, he should knock on the door, wait for a moment, then unlock the bolt, open the door, and look inside while standing outside.*";
P_HTM[10750]="*Sace vihāro uklāpo hoti, mañce vā mañco āropito hoti, pīṭhe vā pīṭhaṃ āropitaṃ hoti, senāsanaṃ upari puñjīkataṃ hoti, sace ussahati, sodhetabbo.**If the dwelling is dirty, and if beds or benches are stacked on top of one another with furniture in a pile on top, he should clean it if he is able.*";
P_HTM[10751]="*Vihāraṃ sodhentena paṭhamaṃ bhūmattharaṇaṃ nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ;**When he is cleaning the dwelling, he should first take out the floor cover and put it aside.*";
P_HTM[10752]="*mañcapaṭipādakā nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbā;**He should take out the bed supports and put them aside.*";
P_HTM[10753]="*bhisibibbohanaṃ nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ;**He should take out the mattress and the pillow and put them aside.*";
P_HTM[10754]="*nisīdanapaccattharaṇaṃ nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ;**He should take out the sitting mat and the sheet and put them aside.*";
P_HTM[10755]="*mañco nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena, asaṅghaṭṭentena kavāṭapiṭṭhaṃ, nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbo;**Holding the bed low, he should carefully take it out without scratching it or knocking it against the door or the door frame, and he should put it aside.*";
P_HTM[10756]="*pīṭhaṃ nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena, asaṅghaṭṭentena kavāṭapiṭṭhaṃ, nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ;**Holding the bench low, he should carefully take it out without scratching it or knocking it against the door or the door frame, and he should put it aside.*";
P_HTM[10757]="*kheḷamallako nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbo;**He should take out the spittoon and put it aside.*";
P_HTM[10758]="*apassenaphalakaṃ nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ.**He should take out the leaning board and put it aside.*";
P_HTM[10759]="*Sace vihāre santānakaṃ hoti, ullokā paṭhamaṃ ohāretabbaṃ, ālokasandhikaṇṇabhāgā pamajjitabbā.**If the dwelling has cobwebs, he should first remove them from the ceiling cloth, and he should then wipe the windows and the corners of the room.*";
P_HTM[10760]="*Sace gerukaparikammakatā bhitti kaṇṇakitā hoti, coḷakaṃ temetvā pīḷetvā pamajjitabbā.**If the walls have been treated with red ocher and they’re moldy, he should moisten a cloth, wring it out, and wipe the walls.*";
P_HTM[10761]="*Sace kāḷavaṇṇakatā bhūmi kaṇṇakitā hoti, coḷakaṃ temetvā pīḷetvā pamajjitabbā.**If the floor has been treated with a black finish and it’s moldy, he should moisten a cloth, wring it out, and wipe the floor.*";
P_HTM[10762]="*Sace akatā hoti bhūmi, udakena paripphositvā sammajjitabbā—**If the floor is untreated, he should sprinkle it with water and then sweep it,*";
P_HTM[10763]="*mā vihāro rajena uhaññīti.**while trying to avoid stirring up dust.*";
P_HTM[10764]="*Saṅkāraṃ vicinitvā ekamantaṃ chaḍḍetabbaṃ.**He should look out for any trash and discard it.*";
P_HTM[10765]="*Bhūmattharaṇaṃ otāpetvā sodhetvā papphoṭetvā atiharitvā yathāṭhāne paññapetabbaṃ.**He should sun the floor cover, clean it, beat it, bring it back inside, and put it back as before.*";
P_HTM[10766]="*Mañcapaṭipādakā otāpetvā pamajjitvā atiharitvā yathāṭhāne ṭhapetabbā.**He should sun the bed supports, wipe them, bring them back inside, and put them back where they were.*";
P_HTM[10767]="*Mañco otāpetvā sodhetvā papphoṭetvā nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena, asaṅghaṭṭentena kavāṭapiṭṭhaṃ, atiharitvā yathāṭhāne paññapetabbo.**He should sun the bed, clean it, and beat it. Holding it low, he should carefully bring it back inside without scratching it or knocking it against the door or the door frame, and he should put as before.*";
P_HTM[10768]="*Pīṭhaṃ otāpetvā sodhetvā papphoṭetvā nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena, asaṅghaṭṭentena kavāṭapiṭṭhaṃ, atiharitvā yathāṭhāne paññapetabbaṃ.**He should sun the bench, clean it, and beat it. Holding it low, he should carefully bring it back inside without scratching it or knocking it against the door or the door frame, and he should put it back as before.*";
P_HTM[10769]="*Bhisibibbohanaṃ otāpetvā sodhetvā papphoṭetvā atiharitvā yathābhāgaṃ paññapetabbaṃ.**He should sun the mattress and the pillow, clean them, beat them, bring them back inside, and put them back as before.*";
P_HTM[10770]="*Nisīdanapaccattharaṇaṃ otāpetvā sodhetvā papphoṭetvā atiharitvā yathābhāgaṃ paññapetabbaṃ.**He should sun the sitting mat and the sheet, clean them, beat them, bring them back inside, and put them back as before.*";
P_HTM[10771]="*Kheḷamallako otāpetvā pamajjitvā atiharitvā yathābhāgaṃ ṭhapetabbo.**He should sun the spittoon, wipe it, bring it back inside, and put it back where it was.*";
P_HTM[10772]="*Apassenaphalakaṃ otāpetvā pamajjitvā atiharitvā yathābhāgaṃ ṭhapetabbaṃ.**He should sun the leaning board, wipe it, bring it back inside, and put it back where it was.*";
P_HTM[10773]="*Pattacīvaraṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ.**He should put away the bowl and robe.*";
P_HTM[10774]="*Pattaṃ nikkhipantena ekena hatthena pattaṃ gahetvā ekena hatthena heṭṭhāmañcaṃ vā heṭṭhāpīṭhaṃ vā parāmasitvā patto nikkhipitabbo.**When putting away the bowl, he should hold the bowl in one hand, feel under the bed or the bench with the other, and then put it away.*";
P_HTM[10775]="*Na ca anantarahitāya bhūmiyā patto nikkhipitabbo.**He shouldn’t put the bowl away on the bare floor.*";
P_HTM[10776]="*Cīvaraṃ nikkhipantena ekena hatthena cīvaraṃ gahetvā ekena hatthena cīvaravaṃsaṃ vā cīvararajjuṃ vā pamajjitvā pārato antaṃ orato bhogaṃ katvā cīvaraṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ.**When putting away the robe, he should hold the robe in one hand, wipe the bamboo robe rack or the clothesline with the other, and then put it away by folding the robe over it, making the ends face the wall and the fold face out.*";
P_HTM[10777]="*Sace puratthimā sarajā vātā vāyanti, puratthimā vātapānā thaketabbā.**If dusty winds are blowing from the east, he should close the windows on the eastern side.*";
P_HTM[10778]="*Sace pacchimā sarajā vātā vāyanti, pacchimā vātapānā thaketabbā.**If dusty winds are blowing from the west, he should close the windows on the western side.*";
P_HTM[10779]="*Sace uttarā sarajā vātā vāyanti, uttarā vātapānā thaketabbā.**If dusty winds are blowing from the north, he should close the windows on the northern side.*";
P_HTM[10780]="*Sace dakkhiṇā sarajā vātā vāyanti, dakkhiṇā vātapānā thaketabbā.**If dusty winds are blowing from the south, he should close the windows on the southern side.*";
P_HTM[10781]="*Sace sītakālo hoti, divā vātapānā vivaritabbā, rattiṃ thaketabbā.**If the weather is cold, he should open the windows during the day and close them at night.*";
P_HTM[10782]="*Sace uṇhakālo hoti, divā vātapānā thaketabbā, rattiṃ vivaritabbā.**If the weather is hot, he should close the windows during the day and open them at night.*";
P_HTM[10783]="*Sace pariveṇaṃ uklāpaṃ hoti, pariveṇaṃ sammajjitabbaṃ.**If the precincts are dirty, he should sweep them.*";
P_HTM[10784]="*Sace koṭṭhako uklāpo hoti, koṭṭhako sammajjitabbo.**If the gateway is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[10785]="*Sace upaṭṭhānasālā uklāpā hoti, upaṭṭhānasālā sammajjitabbā.**If the assembly hall is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[10786]="*Sace aggisālā uklāpā hoti, aggisālā sammajjitabbā.**If the water-boiling shed is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[10787]="*Sace vaccakuṭi uklāpā hoti, vaccakuṭi sammajjitabbā.**If the restroom is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[10788]="*Sace pānīyaṃ na hoti, pānīyaṃ upaṭṭhāpetabbaṃ.**If there is no water for drinking, he should get some.*";
P_HTM[10789]="*Sace paribhojanīyaṃ na hoti, paribhojanīyaṃ upaṭṭhāpetabbaṃ.**If there is no water for washing, he should get some.*";
P_HTM[10790]="*Sace ācamanakumbhiyā udakaṃ na hoti, ācamanakumbhiyā udakaṃ āsiñcitabbaṃ.**If there is no water in the rinsing pot, he should fill it.*";
P_HTM[10791]="*Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, āgantukānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ vattaṃ yathā āgantukehi bhikkhūhi sammā vattitabban”ti.**This is the proper conduct for newly arrived monks.”*";
P_HTM[10792]="*2. Āvāsikavattakathā**2. Discussion of the proper conduct for resident monks*";
P_HTM[10793]="*Tena kho pana samayena āvāsikā bhikkhū āgantuke bhikkhū disvā neva āsanaṃ paññapenti, na pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ pādakathalikaṃ upanikkhipanti, na paccuggantvā pattacīvaraṃ paṭiggaṇhanti, na pānīyena pucchanti, na vuḍḍhatarepi āgantuke bhikkhū abhivādenti, na senāsanaṃ paññapenti.**At that time, when they saw newly arrived monks, the resident monks did not prepare seats, or put out foot stools, foot scrapers, or water for washing the feet. They did not go out to meet them to receive their bowls and robes, or ask if they wanted water to drink. They did not bow down to more senior newly arrived monks or assign dwellings to them.*";
P_HTM[10794]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10795]="*“kathañhi nāma āvāsikā bhikkhū āgantuke bhikkhū disvā neva āsanaṃ paññapessanti, na pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ pādakathalikaṃ upanikkhipissanti, na paccuggantvā pattacīvaraṃ paṭiggahissanti, na pānīyena pucchissanti, vuḍḍhatarepi āgantuke bhikkhū na abhivādessanti, na senāsanaṃ paññapessantī”ti.**“How can the resident monks act like this?”*";
P_HTM[10796]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[10797]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave …pe…**“Is it true, monks, that the resident monks are acting like this?”*";
P_HTM[10798]="*“saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[10799]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[10800]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[10801]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, āvāsikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ vattaṃ paññapessāmi yathā āvāsikehi bhikkhūhi sammā vattitabbaṃ.**“Well then, I will lay down the proper conduct for resident monks.*";
P_HTM[10802]="*Āvāsikena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā āgantukaṃ bhikkhuṃ vuḍḍhataraṃ disvā āsanaṃ paññapetabbaṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ pādakathalikaṃ upanikkhipitabbaṃ, paccuggantvā pattacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ, pānīyena pucchitabbo.**When a resident monk sees a newly arrived monk who is more senior, he should prepare a seat, and put out a foot stool, a foot scraper, and water for washing the feet. He should go out to meet him to receive his bowl and robe, and ask if he wants water to drink.*";
P_HTM[10803]="*Sace ussahati, upāhanā puñchitabbā.**If he is able, he should wipe his sandals,*";
P_HTM[10804]="*Upāhanā puñchantena paṭhamaṃ sukkhena coḷakena puñchitabbā, pacchā allena.**first with a dry cloth and then a wet one.*";
P_HTM[10805]="*Upāhanāpuñchanacoḷakaṃ dhovitvā ekamantaṃ vissajjetabbaṃ.**He should wash the cloth and put it aside.*";
P_HTM[10806]="*Āgantuko bhikkhu vuḍḍhataro abhivādetabbo.**If the newly arrived monk is more senior, the resident monk should bow down to him.*";
P_HTM[10807]="*Senāsanaṃ paññapetabbaṃ—**He should assign a dwelling,*";
P_HTM[10808]="*‘etaṃ te senāsanaṃ pāpuṇātī’ti.**tell him where it is,*";
P_HTM[10809]="*Ajjhāvuṭṭhaṃ vā anajjhāvuṭṭhaṃ vā ācikkhitabbaṃ.**and inform him whether it’s occupied or not.*";
P_HTM[10810]="*Gocaro ācikkhitabbo.**He should tell him where to go for alms*";
P_HTM[10811]="*Agocaro ācikkhitabbo.**and where to avoid,*";
P_HTM[10812]="*Sekkhasammatāni kulāni ācikkhitabbāni.**and about any families designated as “in training”.*";
P_HTM[10813]="*Vaccaṭṭhānaṃ ācikkhitabbaṃ.**He should point out the place for defecating*";
P_HTM[10814]="*Passāvaṭṭhānaṃ ācikkhitabbaṃ.**and the place for urinating,*";
P_HTM[10815]="*Pānīyaṃ ācikkhitabbaṃ.**the water for drinking*";
P_HTM[10816]="*Paribhojanīyaṃ ācikkhitabbaṃ.**and the water for washing,*";
P_HTM[10817]="*Kattaradaṇḍo ācikkhitabbo.**and the walking sticks.*";
P_HTM[10818]="*Saṅghassa katikasaṇṭhānaṃ ācikkhitabbaṃ—**He should tell him about the Sangha’s agreements*";
P_HTM[10819]="*‘imaṃ kālaṃ pavisitabbaṃ, imaṃ kālaṃ nikkhamitabban’ti.**concerning the right time to enter and the right time to leave.*";
P_HTM[10820]="*Sace navako hoti, nisinnakeneva ācikkhitabbaṃ—**If the newly arrived monk is more junior, the resident monk should remain seated*";
P_HTM[10821]="*‘atra pattaṃ nikkhipāhi, atra cīvaraṃ nikkhipāhi, idaṃ āsanaṃ nisīdāhī’ti.**while telling him where to put his bowl and robe, and which seat to sit on.*";
P_HTM[10822]="*Pānīyaṃ ācikkhitabbaṃ.**He should point out the water for drinking*";
P_HTM[10823]="*Paribhojanīyaṃ ācikkhitabbaṃ.**and the water for washing,*";
P_HTM[10824]="*Upāhanāpuñchanacoḷakaṃ ācikkhitabbaṃ.**as well as a sandal-wiping cloth.*";
P_HTM[10825]="*Āgantuko bhikkhu navako abhivādāpetabbo.**If the newly arrived monk is more junior, he should bow down to the resident monk.*";
P_HTM[10826]="*Senāsanaṃ ācikkhitabbaṃ—**The resident monk should tell him*";
P_HTM[10827]="*‘etaṃ te senāsanaṃ pāpuṇātī’ti.**where his dwelling is*";
P_HTM[10828]="*Ajjhāvuṭṭhaṃ vā anajjhāvuṭṭhaṃ vā ācikkhitabbaṃ.**and whether it’s occupied or not.*";
P_HTM[10829]="*Gocaro ācikkhitabbo.**He should tell him where to go for alms*";
P_HTM[10830]="*Agocaro ācikkhitabbo.**and where to avoid,*";
P_HTM[10831]="*Sekkhasammatāni kulāni ācikkhitabbāni.**and about any families designated as “in training”.*";
P_HTM[10832]="*Vaccaṭṭhānaṃ ācikkhitabbaṃ.**He should point out the place for defecating*";
P_HTM[10833]="*Passāvaṭṭhānaṃ ācikkhitabbaṃ.**and the place for urinating,*";
P_HTM[10834]="*Pānīyaṃ ācikkhitabbaṃ.**the water for drinking*";
P_HTM[10835]="*Paribhojanīyaṃ ācikkhitabbaṃ.**and the water for washing,*";
P_HTM[10836]="*Kattaradaṇḍo ācikkhitabbo.**and the walking sticks.*";
P_HTM[10837]="*Saṅghassa katikasaṇṭhānaṃ ācikkhitabbaṃ—**He should tell him about the Sangha’s agreements*";
P_HTM[10838]="*‘imaṃ kālaṃ pavisitabbaṃ, imaṃ kālaṃ nikkhamitabban’ti.**concerning the right time to enter and the right time to leave.*";
P_HTM[10839]="*Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, āvāsikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ vattaṃ yathā āvāsikehi bhikkhūhi sammā vattitabban”ti.**This is the proper conduct for resident monks.”*";
P_HTM[10840]="*3. Gamikavattakathā**3. Discussion of the proper conduct for departing monks*";
P_HTM[10841]="*Tena kho pana samayena gamikā bhikkhū dārubhaṇḍaṃ mattikābhaṇḍaṃ appaṭisāmetvā dvāravātapānaṃ vivaritvā senāsanaṃ anāpucchā pakkamanti.**At that time the monks departed without putting the wooden and ceramic goods in order, while leaving the door and the windows open, and without taking leave.*";
P_HTM[10842]="*Dārubhaṇḍaṃ mattikābhaṇḍaṃ nassati.**Wooden and ceramic goods were lost*";
P_HTM[10843]="*Senāsanaṃ aguttaṃ hoti.**and the dwelling was unprotected.*";
P_HTM[10844]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10845]="*“kathañhi nāma gamikā bhikkhū dārubhaṇḍaṃ mattikābhaṇḍaṃ appaṭisāmetvā dvāravātapānaṃ vivaritvā senāsanaṃ anāpucchā pakkamissanti.**“How can the departing monks act like this?”*";
P_HTM[10846]="*Dārubhaṇḍaṃ mattikābhaṇḍaṃ nassati.* **";
P_HTM[10847]="*Senāsanaṃ aguttaṃ hotī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[10848]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[10849]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave …pe…**“Is it true, monks, that the departing monks are acting like this?”*";
P_HTM[10850]="*“saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[10851]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[10852]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[10853]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, gamikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ vattaṃ paññapessāmi yathā gamikehi bhikkhūhi sammā vattitabbaṃ.**“Well then, I will lay down the proper conduct for departing monks.*";
P_HTM[10854]="*Gamikena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā dārubhaṇḍaṃ mattikābhaṇḍaṃ paṭisāmetvā dvāravātapānaṃ thaketvā senāsanaṃ āpucchā pakkamitabbaṃ.**Before he departs, a monk should put the wooden and ceramic goods in order, close the door and the windows, and take leave.*";
P_HTM[10855]="*Sace bhikkhu na hoti, sāmaṇero āpucchitabbo.**If there are no monks, he should take leave of a novice monk;*";
P_HTM[10856]="*Sace sāmaṇero na hoti, ārāmiko āpucchitabbo.**if there are no novice monks, he should take leave of a monastery worker;*";
P_HTM[10857]="*Sace ārāmiko na hoti, upāsako āpucchitabbo.**if there are no monastery workers, he should take leave of a lay follower.*";
P_HTM[10858]="*Sace na hoti bhikkhu vā sāmaṇero vā ārāmiko vā upāsako vā, catūsu pāsāṇesu mañcaṃ paññapetvā mañce mañcaṃ āropetvā pīṭhe pīṭhaṃ āropetvā senāsanaṃ upari puñjaṃ karitvā dārubhaṇḍaṃ mattikābhaṇḍaṃ paṭisāmetvā dvāravātapānaṃ thaketvā pakkamitabbaṃ.**If there are no monks, novice monks, monastery workers, or lay followers, he should place the bed on four rocks. He should stack the beds or benches on top of one another, with the furniture in a pile on top, and put away the wooden and ceramic goods. He should close the door and the windows, and then depart.*";
P_HTM[10859]="*Sace vihāro ovassati, sace ussahati, chādetabbo, ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—**If rain enters the dwelling, he should cover it if he is able, or he should make an effort*";
P_HTM[10860]="*‘kinti nu kho vihāro chādiyethā’ti.**to have it covered.*";
P_HTM[10861]="*Evañcetaṃ labhetha, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ.**If this works out, all is well.*";
P_HTM[10862]="*No ce labhetha, yo deso anovassako hoti, tattha catūsu pāsāṇesu mañcaṃ paññapetvā mañce mañcaṃ āropetvā pīṭhe pīṭhaṃ āropetvā senāsanaṃ upari puñjaṃ karitvā dārubhaṇḍaṃ mattikābhaṇḍaṃ paṭisāmetvā dvāravātapānaṃ thaketvā pakkamitabbaṃ.**If not, he should place the bed on four rocks in an area that isn’t getting wet. He should then stack the beds or benches on top of one another, with the furniture in a pile on top, and put away the wooden and ceramic goods. He should close the door and the windows, and then depart.*";
P_HTM[10863]="*Sace sabbo vihāro ovassati, sace ussahati, senāsanaṃ gāmaṃ atiharitabbaṃ, ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—**If the whole dwelling is getting wet, he should carry the furniture to the village if he is able, or he should make an effort*";
P_HTM[10864]="*‘kinti nu kho senāsanaṃ gāmaṃ atihariyethā’ti.**to have it carried to the village.*";
P_HTM[10865]="*Evañcetaṃ labhetha, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ.**If this works out, all is well.*";
P_HTM[10866]="*No ce labhetha, ajjhokāse catūsu pāsāṇesu mañcaṃ paññapetvā mañce mañcaṃ āropetvā pīṭhe pīṭhaṃ āropetvā senāsanaṃ upari puñjaṃ karitvā dārubhaṇḍaṃ mattikābhaṇḍaṃ paṭisāmetvā tiṇena vā paṇṇena vā paṭicchādetvā pakkamitabbaṃ—**If not, he should place the bed on four rocks outside. He should then stack the beds or benches on top of one another, with the furniture in a pile on top, and he should put away the wooden and ceramic goods. He should cover it all with grass and leaves and then depart,*";
P_HTM[10867]="*appeva nāma aṅgānipi seseyyunti.**thinking, ‘Hopefully the requisites will be okay.’*";
P_HTM[10868]="*Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, gamikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ vattaṃ yathā gamikehi bhikkhūhi sammā vattitabban”ti.**This is the proper conduct for departing monks.”*";
P_HTM[10869]="*4. Anumodanavattakathā**4. Discussion of the proper conduct in connection with the expression of appreciation*";
P_HTM[10870]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū bhattagge na anumodanti.**At that time the monks did not express their appreciation in the dining hall.*";
P_HTM[10871]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10872]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā bhattagge na anumodissantī”ti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics not express their appreciation in the dining hall?”*";
P_HTM[10873]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people*";
P_HTM[10874]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**and they told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[10875]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**The Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[10876]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhattagge anumoditun”ti.**“You should express your appreciation in the dining hall.”*";
P_HTM[10877]="*Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The monks thought,*";
P_HTM[10878]="*“kena nu kho bhattagge anumoditabban”ti?**“Who should give the expression of appreciation?”*";
P_HTM[10879]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[10880]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**He gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[10881]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, therena bhikkhunā bhattagge anumoditun”ti.**“The most senior monk should give the expression of appreciation in the dining hall.”*";
P_HTM[10882]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa pūgassa saṅghabhattaṃ hoti.**Soon afterwards a certain association was offering a meal to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[10883]="*Āyasmā sāriputto saṅghatthero hoti.**Venerable Sāriputta was the most senior monk.*";
P_HTM[10884]="*Bhikkhū—* **";
P_HTM[10885]="*“bhagavatā anuññātaṃ therena bhikkhunā bhattagge anumoditun”ti—**Because the Buddha had said the most senior monk should give the expression of appreciation,*";
P_HTM[10886]="*āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ ekakaṃ ohāya pakkamiṃsu.**the monks left, leaving Sāriputta behind by himself.*";
P_HTM[10887]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto te manusse paṭisammoditvā pacchā ekako agamāsi.**After giving the expression of appreciation, he left by himself.*";
P_HTM[10888]="*Addasā kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ dūratova ekakaṃ āgacchantaṃ.**The Buddha saw him coming*";
P_HTM[10889]="*Disvāna āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca—**and asked,*";
P_HTM[10890]="*“kacci, sāriputta, bhattaṃ iddhaṃ ahosī”ti?**“Did the meal go well?”*";
P_HTM[10891]="*“Iddhaṃ kho, bhante, bhattaṃ ahosi;**“The meal went well, Venerable Sir,*";
P_HTM[10892]="*api ca maṃ bhikkhū ekakaṃ ohāya pakkantā”ti.**but the monks all left leaving me behind by myself.”*";
P_HTM[10893]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[10894]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhattagge catūhi pañcahi therānutherehi bhikkhūhi āgametun”ti.**“The four or five most senior monks should wait in the dining hall.”*";
P_HTM[10895]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro thero bhattagge vaccito āgamesi.**On one occasion a senior monk who needed to defecate was waiting in the dining hall.*";
P_HTM[10896]="*So vaccaṃ sandhāretuṃ asakkonto mucchito papati.**Being unable to hold out, he fainted and fell over.*";
P_HTM[10897]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[10898]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, sati karaṇīye ānantarikaṃ bhikkhuṃ āpucchitvā gantun”ti.**“When there is something to be done, I allow you to go after taking leave of the monk sitting next to you.”*";
P_HTM[10899]="*5. Bhattaggavattakathā**5. Discussion of the proper conduct in relation to the dining hall*";
P_HTM[10900]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū dunnivatthā duppārutā anākappasampannā bhattaggaṃ gacchanti, vokkammapi therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ purato purato gacchanti, therepi bhikkhū anupakhajja nisīdanti, navepi bhikkhū āsanena paṭibāhanti, saṅghāṭimpi ottharitvā antaraghare nisīdanti.**At that time the monks from the group of six went to the dining hall shabbily dressed and improper in appearance; going the wrong way, they went ahead of the senior monks; they sat down encroaching on the senior monks; they blocked the junior monks from seats; and they spread out their upper robes and sat on them in inhabited areas.*";
P_HTM[10901]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10902]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū dunnivatthā duppārutā anākappasampannā bhattaggaṃ gacchissanti, vokkammapi therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ purato purato gacchissanti, therepi bhikkhū anupakhajja nisīdissanti, navepi bhikkhū āsanenapi paṭibāhissanti, saṅghāṭimpi ottharitvā antaraghare nisīdissantī”ti.**“How can the monks from the group of six act like this?”*";
P_HTM[10903]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[10904]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū dunnivatthā duppārutā anākappasampannā bhattaggaṃ gacchanti, vokkammapi therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ purato purato gacchanti, therepi bhikkhū anupakhajja nisīdanti, navepi bhikkhū āsanena paṭibāhanti, saṅghāṭimpi ottharitvā antaraghare nisīdantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the monks from the group of six are acting like this?”*";
P_HTM[10905]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[10906]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[10907]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[10908]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ bhattaggavattaṃ paññapessāmi yathā bhikkhūhi bhattagge sammā vattitabbaṃ.**“Well then, I will lay down the proper conduct in relation to the dining hall.*";
P_HTM[10909]="*Sace ārāme kālo ārocito hoti, timaṇḍalaṃ paṭicchādentena parimaṇḍalaṃ nivāsetvā kāyabandhanaṃ bandhitvā saguṇaṃ katvā saṅghāṭiyo pārupitvā gaṇṭhikaṃ paṭimuñcitvā dhovitvā pattaṃ gahetvā sādhukaṃ ataramānena gāmo pavisitabbo.**In a monastery where the time for departure is announced, a monk should put on his sarong evenly all around, covering the navel and the knees. He should put on a belt. Putting the upper robes together, overlapping each other edge-to-edge, he should put them on and fasten the toggle. He should wash his bowl, bring it along, and enter the village carefully and without hurry.*";
P_HTM[10910]="*Na vokkamma therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ purato purato gantabbaṃ.**He should not go the wrong way and walk in front of the senior monks.*";
P_HTM[10911]="*Suppaṭicchannena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**He should walk well-covered in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10912]="*Susaṃvutena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should walk well-restrained in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10913]="*Okkhittacakkhunā antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should walk with lowered eyes in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10914]="*Na ukkhittakāya antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should lift up his robe while walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10915]="*Na ujjagghikāya antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not laugh loudly while walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10916]="*Appasaddena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not be noisy while walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10917]="*Na kāyappacālakaṃ antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not sway his body while walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10918]="*Na bāhuppacālakaṃ antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not swing his arms while walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10919]="*Na sīsappacālakaṃ antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not sway his head while walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10920]="*Na khambhakatena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not walk with arms akimbo in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10921]="*Na oguṇṭhitena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not cover his head while walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10922]="*Na ukkuṭikāya antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not squat on his heels while walking in inhabited areas.*";
P_HTM[10923]="*Suppaṭicchannena antaraghare nisīditabbaṃ.**He should sit well-covered in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10924]="*Susaṃvutena antaraghare nisīditabbaṃ.**he should sit well-restrained in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10925]="*Okkhittacakkhunā antaraghare nisīditabbaṃ.**he should sit with lowered eyes in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10926]="*Na ukkhittakāya antaraghare nisīditabbaṃ**he should not lift his robes while sitting in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10927]="*na ujjagghikāya antaraghare nisīditabbaṃ,**he should not laugh loudly while sitting in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10928]="*appasaddena antaraghare nisīditabbaṃ.**he should not be noisy while sitting in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10929]="*Na kāyappacālakaṃ antaraghare nisīditabbaṃ.**he should not sway his body while sitting in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10930]="*Na bāhuppacālakaṃ antaraghare nisīditabbaṃ.**he should not swing his arms while sitting in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10931]="*Na sīsappacālakaṃ antaraghare nisīditabbaṃ.**he should not sway his head while sitting in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10932]="*Na khambhakatena antaraghare nisīditabbaṃ.**he should not sit with arms akimbo in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10933]="*Na oguṇṭhitena antaraghare nisīditabbaṃ.**he should not cover his head while sitting in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10934]="*Na pallatthikāya antaraghare nisīditabbaṃ.**he should not clasp his knees while sitting in inhabited areas.*";
P_HTM[10935]="*Na there bhikkhū anupakhajja nisīditabbaṃ.**He should not sit encroaching on the senior monks*";
P_HTM[10936]="*Na navā bhikkhū āsanena paṭibāhitabbā.**or blocking the junior monks from seats.*";
P_HTM[10937]="*Na saṅghāṭiṃ ottharitvā antaraghare nisīditabbaṃ.**He should not spread out his upper robe and sit on it in inhabited areas.*";
P_HTM[10938]="*Udake diyyamāne ubhohi hatthehi pattaṃ paṭiggahetvā udakaṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ.**When given water, he should receive it by holding his bowl with both hands.*";
P_HTM[10939]="*Nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena patto dhovitabbo.**Holding the bowl low, he should rinse it carefully without scratching it.*";
P_HTM[10940]="*Sace udakappaṭiggāhako hoti, nīcaṃ katvā udakappaṭiggahe udakaṃ āsiñcitabbaṃ—**If there is someone to receive the water, he should hold his bowl low and pour the water into the container,*";
P_HTM[10941]="*mā udakappaṭiggāhako udakena osiñci, mā sāmantā bhikkhū udakena osiñciṃsu, mā saṅghāṭi udakena osiñcīti.**trying to avoid splashing the person receiving the water, the monks sitting nearby, or his upper robe.*";
P_HTM[10942]="*Sace udakappaṭiggāhako na hoti, nīcaṃ katvā chamāya udakaṃ āsiñcitabbaṃ—**If there is no one to receive the water, he should hold his bowl low and pour the water on the ground,*";
P_HTM[10943]="*mā sāmantā bhikkhū udakena osiñciṃsu, mā saṅghāṭi udakena osiñcīti.**trying to avoid splashing the monks sitting nearby or his upper robe.*";
P_HTM[10944]="*Odane diyyamāne ubhohi hatthehi pattaṃ paṭiggahetvā odano paṭiggahetabbo, sūpassa okāso kātabbo.**When given rice, he should receive it by holding his bowl with both hands, leaving room for the curry.*";
P_HTM[10945]="*Sace hoti sappi vā telaṃ vā uttaribhaṅgaṃ vā, therena vattabbo—**If there is ghee, oil, or special curry, the senior monk should say,*";
P_HTM[10946]="*‘sabbesaṃ samakaṃ sampādehī’ti.**‘Everyone gets an equal share.’*";
P_HTM[10947]="*Sakkaccaṃ piṇḍapāto paṭiggahetabbo.**He should receive the almsfood respectfully;*";
P_HTM[10948]="*Pattasaññinā piṇḍapāto paṭiggahetabbo.**he should receive the almsfood with attention on the bowl;*";
P_HTM[10949]="*Samasūpako piṇḍapāto paṭiggahetabbo.**he should receive the almsfood with the right proportion of bean curry;*";
P_HTM[10950]="*Samatittiko piṇḍapāto paṭiggahetabbo.**he should receive the almsfood on an even level.*";
P_HTM[10951]="*Na tāva therena bhuñjitabbaṃ yāva na sabbesaṃ odano sampatto hoti.**The senior monk should not start eating until everyone has received rice.*";
P_HTM[10952]="*Sakkaccaṃ piṇḍapāto bhuñjitabbo.**A monk should eat the almsfood respectfully;*";
P_HTM[10953]="*Pattasaññinā piṇḍapāto bhuñjitabbo.**he should eat the almsfood with attention on the bowl;*";
P_HTM[10954]="*Sapadānaṃ piṇḍapāto bhuñjitabbo.**he should eat the almsfood in order;*";
P_HTM[10955]="*Samasūpako piṇḍapāto bhuñjitabbo.**he should eat the almsfood with the right proportion of bean curry;*";
P_HTM[10956]="*Na thūpakato omadditvā piṇḍapāto bhuñjitabbo.**he should not eat almsfood picking from a heap;*";
P_HTM[10957]="*Na sūpaṃ vā byañjanaṃ vā odanena paṭicchādetabbaṃ bhiyyokamyataṃ upādāya.**he should not cover the various kinds of curry with rice because he wants more;*";
P_HTM[10958]="*Na sūpaṃ vā odanaṃ vā agilānena attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjitabbaṃ.**when not sick, he should not ask for bean curry and rice for himself and then eat it;*";
P_HTM[10959]="*Na ujjhānasaññinā paresaṃ patto oloketabbo.**he should not look at another’s bowl finding fault;*";
P_HTM[10960]="*Nātimahanto kabaḷo kātabbo.**he should not make a mouthful that’s too large;*";
P_HTM[10961]="*Parimaṇḍalo ālopo kātabbo.**he should make rounded mouthfuls;*";
P_HTM[10962]="*Na anāhaṭe kabaḷe mukhadvāraṃ vivaritabbaṃ.**he should not open his mouth when a mouthful hasn’t been brought to it;*";
P_HTM[10963]="*Na bhuñjamānena sabbo hattho mukhe pakkhipitabbo.**he should not put the whole hand in his mouth while eating;*";
P_HTM[10964]="*Na sakabaḷena mukhena byāharitabbaṃ.**he should not speak with food in his mouth;*";
P_HTM[10965]="*Na piṇḍukkhepakaṃ bhuñjitabbaṃ.**he should not eat from a lifted ball of food;*";
P_HTM[10966]="*Na kabaḷāvacchedakaṃ bhuñjitabbaṃ.**he should not eat breaking up mouthfuls;*";
P_HTM[10967]="*Na avagaṇḍakārakaṃ bhuñjitabbaṃ.**he should not eat stuffing the cheeks;*";
P_HTM[10968]="*Na hatthaniddhunakaṃ bhuñjitabbaṃ.**he should not eat shaking the hands;*";
P_HTM[10969]="*Na sitthāvakārakaṃ bhuñjitabbaṃ.**he should not eat scattering rice about;*";
P_HTM[10970]="*Na jivhānicchārakaṃ bhuñjitabbaṃ.**he should not eat sticking out his tongue;*";
P_HTM[10971]="*Na capucapukārakaṃ bhuñjitabbaṃ.**he should not chomp while eating;*";
P_HTM[10972]="*Na surusurukārakaṃ bhuñjitabbaṃ.**he should not slurp while eating;*";
P_HTM[10973]="*Na hatthanillehakaṃ bhuñjitabbaṃ.**he should not eat licking his hands;*";
P_HTM[10974]="*Na pattanillehakaṃ bhuñjitabbaṃ.**he should not eat licking his bowl;*";
P_HTM[10975]="*Na oṭṭhanillehakaṃ bhuñjitabbaṃ.**he should not eat licking his lips.*";
P_HTM[10976]="*Na sāmisena hatthena pānīyathālako paṭiggahetabbo.**He should not receive the drinking-water vessel with a hand soiled with food.*";
P_HTM[10977]="*Na tāva therena udakaṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ yāva na sabbeva bhuttāvino honti.**The senior monk should not receive water for washing until all the monks are finished eating.*";
P_HTM[10978]="*Udake diyyamāne ubhohi hatthehi pattaṃ paṭiggahetvā udakaṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ.**When given water, a monk should receive it by holding his bowl with both hands.*";
P_HTM[10979]="*Nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena patto dhovitabbo.**Holding the bowl low, he should rinse it carefully without scratching it.*";
P_HTM[10980]="*Sace udakappaṭiggāhako hoti, nīcaṃ katvā udakappaṭiggahe udakaṃ āsiñcitabbaṃ—**If there is someone to receive the water, he should hold his bowl low and pour the water into the container,*";
P_HTM[10981]="*mā udakappaṭiggāhako udakena osiñci, mā sāmantā bhikkhū udakena osiñciṃsu, mā saṅghāṭi udakena osiñcīti.**trying to avoid splashing the person receiving the water, the monks sitting nearby, or his upper robe.*";
P_HTM[10982]="*Sace udakappaṭiggāhako na hoti, nīcaṃ katvā chamāya udakaṃ āsiñcitabbaṃ—**If there is no one to receive the water, he should hold his bowl low and pour the water on the ground,*";
P_HTM[10983]="*mā sāmantā bhikkhū udakena osiñciṃsu, mā saṅghāṭi udakena osiñcīti.**trying to avoid splashing the monks sitting nearby or his upper robe.*";
P_HTM[10984]="*Na sasitthakaṃ pattadhovanaṃ antaraghare chaḍḍetabbaṃ.**He should not discard bowl-washing water containing rice in inhabited areas.*";
P_HTM[10985]="*Nivattantena navakehi bhikkhūhi paṭhamataraṃ nivattitabbaṃ, pacchā therehi.**When returning, the junior monks should go first and then the senior monks.*";
P_HTM[10986]="*Suppaṭicchannena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**A monk should be well-covered when walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10987]="*Susaṃvutena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should be well-restrained when walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10988]="*Okkhittacakkhunā antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should walk with lowered eyes in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10989]="*Na ukkhittakāya antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not walk with his robe lifted up in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10990]="*Na ujjagghikāya antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not laugh loudly when walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10991]="*Appasaddena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not be noisy when walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10992]="*Na kāyappacālakaṃ antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not sway his body when walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10993]="*Na bāhuppacālakaṃ antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not swing his arms when walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10994]="*Na sīsappacālakaṃ antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not sway his head when walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10995]="*Na khambhakatena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not walk with arms akimbo in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10996]="*Na oguṇṭhitena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not walk with his head covered in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[10997]="*Na ukkuṭikāya antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not squat on his heels when walking in inhabited areas.*";
P_HTM[10998]="*Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ bhattaggavattaṃ yathā bhikkhūhi bhattagge sammā vattitabban”ti.**This is the proper conduct in relation to the dining hall.”*";
P_HTM[10999]="*Paṭhamabhāṇavāro niṭṭhito.**The first section for recitation is finished.*";
P_HTM[11000]="*6. Piṇḍacārikavattakathā**6. Discussion of the proper conduct for alms-collectors*";
P_HTM[11001]="*Tena kho pana samayena piṇḍacārikā bhikkhū dunnivatthā duppārutā anākappasampannā piṇḍāya caranti, asallakkhetvāpi nivesanaṃ pavisanti, asallakkhetvāpi nikkhamanti, atisahasāpi pavisanti, atisahasāpi nikkhamanti, atidūrepi tiṭṭhanti, accāsannepi tiṭṭhanti, aticirampi tiṭṭhanti, atilahumpi nivattanti.**At that time there were alms-collecting monks who were shabbily dressed and improper in appearance. They entered and left houses without being attentive; they entered and left too hastily; they stood too far away or too close; they waited too long or left too soon.*";
P_HTM[11002]="*Aññataropi piṇḍacāriko bhikkhu asallakkhetvā nivesanaṃ pāvisi.**On one occasion a certain monk entered a house without being attentive.*";
P_HTM[11003]="*So ca dvāraṃ maññamāno aññataraṃ ovarakaṃ pāvisi.**Thinking it was the main door, he entered a room*";
P_HTM[11004]="*Tasmimpi ovarake itthī naggā uttānā nipannā hoti.**where a woman was sleeping naked.*";
P_HTM[11005]="*Addasā kho so bhikkhu taṃ itthiṃ naggaṃ uttānaṃ nipannaṃ.**The monk saw her*";
P_HTM[11006]="*Disvāna—* **";
P_HTM[11007]="*“nayidaṃ dvāraṃ, ovarakaṃ idan”ti tamhā ovarakā nikkhami.**and left the room.*";
P_HTM[11008]="*Addasā kho tassā itthiyā sāmiko taṃ itthiṃ naggaṃ uttānaṃ nipannaṃ.**Seeing her lying there,*";
P_HTM[11009]="*Disvāna—* **";
P_HTM[11010]="*“iminā me bhikkhunā pajāpatī dūsitā”ti taṃ bhikkhuṃ gahetvā ākoṭesi.**the woman’s husband thought, “My wife has been raped by this monk,” and he took hold of that monk and gave him a beating.*";
P_HTM[11011]="*Atha kho sā itthī tena saddena paṭibujjhitvā taṃ purisaṃ etadavoca—**The woman woke up from the noise and asked her husband,*";
P_HTM[11012]="*“kissa tvaṃ, ayya, imaṃ bhikkhuṃ ākoṭesī”ti?**“Why are you beating this monk?”*";
P_HTM[11013]="*“Imināsi tvaṃ bhikkhunā dūsitā”ti?**“Didn’t he rape you?”*";
P_HTM[11014]="*“Nāhaṃ, ayya, iminā bhikkhunā dūsitā;**“No he didn’t;*";
P_HTM[11015]="*akārako so bhikkhū”ti taṃ bhikkhuṃ muñcāpesi.**he didn’t do anything.” And she had him release that monk.*";
P_HTM[11016]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**The monk returned to the monastery and told the monks what had happened.*";
P_HTM[11017]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11018]="*“kathañhi nāma piṇḍacārikā bhikkhū dunnivatthā duppārutā anākappasampannā piṇḍāya carissanti, asallakkhetvāpi nivesanaṃ pavisissanti, asallakkhetvāpi nikkhamissanti, atisahasāpi pavisissanti, atisahasāpi nikkhamissanti, atidūrepi tiṭṭhissanti, accāsannepi tiṭṭhissanti, aticirampi tiṭṭhissanti, atilahumpi nivattissantī”ti.**“How can the alms-collecting monks act like this?”*";
P_HTM[11019]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[11020]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave …pe…**“Is it true, monks, that the alms-collecting monks are acting like this?”*";
P_HTM[11021]="*“saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[11022]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[11023]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[11024]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, piṇḍacārikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ vattaṃ paññapessāmi yathā piṇḍacārikehi bhikkhūhi sammā vattitabbaṃ.**“Well then, I will lay down the proper conduct for alms-collecting monks.*";
P_HTM[11025]="*Piṇḍacārikena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā—**When an alms-collecting monk is about to enter the village,*";
P_HTM[11026]="*‘idāni gāmaṃ pavisissāmī’ti timaṇḍalaṃ paṭicchādentena parimaṇḍalaṃ nivāsetvā kāyabandhanaṃ bandhitvā saguṇaṃ katvā saṅghāṭiyo pārupitvā gaṇṭhikaṃ paṭimuñcitvā dhovitvā pattaṃ gahetvā sādhukaṃ ataramānena gāmo pavisitabbo.**he should put on his sarong evenly all around, covering the navel and the knees. He should put on a belt. Putting the upper robes together, overlapping each other edge-to-edge, he should put them on and fasten the toggle. He should wash his bowl, bring it along, and enter the village carefully and without hurry.*";
P_HTM[11027]="*Suppaṭicchannena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**He should be well-covered when walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11028]="*Susaṃvutena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should be well-restrained when walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11029]="*Okkhittacakkhunā antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should walk with lowered eyes in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11030]="*Na ukkhittakāya antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not walk with his robe lifted up in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11031]="*Na ujjagghikāya antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not laugh loudly when walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11032]="*Appasaddena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not be noisy when walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11033]="*Na kāyappacālakaṃ antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not sway his body when walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11034]="*Na bāhuppacālakaṃ antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not swing his arms when walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11035]="*Na sīsappacālakaṃ antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not sway his head when walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11036]="*Na khambhakatena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not walk with arms akimbo in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11037]="*Na oguṇṭhitena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not walk with his head covered in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11038]="*Na ukkuṭikāya antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not squat on his heels when walking in inhabited areas.*";
P_HTM[11039]="*Nivesanaṃ pavisantena sallakkhetabbaṃ—**When entering a house,*";
P_HTM[11040]="*‘iminā pavisissāmi, iminā nikkhamissāmī’ti.**he should be attentive to where to enter and where to leave.*";
P_HTM[11041]="*Nātisahasā pavisitabbaṃ.**He should not enter*";
P_HTM[11042]="*Nātisahasā nikkhamitabbaṃ.**or leave too hastily;*";
P_HTM[11043]="*Nātidūre ṭhātabbaṃ.**he should not stand too far away*";
P_HTM[11044]="*Nāccāsanne ṭhātabbaṃ.**or too close;*";
P_HTM[11045]="*Nāticiraṃ ṭhātabbaṃ.**he should not wait too long*";
P_HTM[11046]="*Nātilahuṃ nivattitabbaṃ.**or leave too soon.*";
P_HTM[11047]="*Ṭhitakena sallakkhetabbaṃ—**While waiting,*";
P_HTM[11048]="*‘bhikkhaṃ dātukāmā vā adātukāmā vā’ti.**he should be attentive to whether they wish to give alms or not.*";
P_HTM[11049]="*Sace kammaṃ vā nikkhipati, āsanā vā vuṭṭhāti, kaṭacchuṃ vā parāmasati, bhājanaṃ vā parāmasati, ṭhapeti vā—dātukāmassāti ṭhātabbaṃ.**If they put down their work, get up from their seat, take hold of a serving spoon or a vessel, or they tell him to wait, then he should assume they wish to give, and he should wait.*";
P_HTM[11050]="*Bhikkhāya diyyamānāya vāmena hatthena saṅghāṭiṃ uccāretvā dakkhiṇena hatthena pattaṃ paṇāmetvā ubhohi hatthehi pattaṃ paṭiggahetvā bhikkhā paṭiggahetabbā.**When they give him almsfood, he should lift up his upper robe with his left hand, stretch out his bowl with his right hand, and receive the alms while holding the bowl with both hands.*";
P_HTM[11051]="*Na ca bhikkhādāyikāya mukhaṃ ulloketabbaṃ.**He should not look the donor in the face.*";
P_HTM[11052]="*Sallakkhetabbaṃ—**He should be attentive*";
P_HTM[11053]="*‘sūpaṃ dātukāmā vā adātukāmā vā’ti.**to whether they wish to give curry or not.*";
P_HTM[11054]="*Sace kaṭacchuṃ vā parāmasati, bhājanaṃ vā parāmasati, ṭhapeti vā—**If they take hold of a serving spoon or a vessel, or they tell him to wait,*";
P_HTM[11055]="*dātukāmassāti ṭhātabbaṃ.**then he should assume they wish to give, and he should wait.*";
P_HTM[11056]="*Bhikkhāya dinnāya saṅghāṭiyā pattaṃ paṭicchādetvā sādhukaṃ ataramānena nivattitabbaṃ.**When they have given alms, he should cover the bowl with his upper robe, and leave carefully and without hurry.*";
P_HTM[11057]="*Suppaṭicchannena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**He should be well-covered when walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11058]="*Susaṃvutena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should be well-restrained when walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11059]="*Okkhittacakkhunā antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should walk with lowered eyes in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11060]="*Na ukkhittakāya antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not walk with his robe lifted up in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11061]="*Na ujjagghikāya antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not laugh loudly when walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11062]="*Appasaddena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not be noisy when walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11063]="*Na kāyappacālakaṃ antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not sway his body when walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11064]="*Na bāhuppacālakaṃ antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not swing his arms when walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11065]="*Na sīsappacālakaṃ antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not sway his head when walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11066]="*Na khambhakatena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not walk with arms akimbo in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11067]="*Na oguṇṭhitena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not walk with his head covered in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11068]="*Na ukkuṭikāya antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not squat on his heels when walking in inhabited areas.*";
P_HTM[11069]="*Yo paṭhamaṃ gāmato piṇḍāya paṭikkamati, tena āsanaṃ paññapetabbaṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ pādakathalikaṃ upanikkhipitabbaṃ, avakkārapāti dhovitvā upaṭṭhāpetabbā, pānīyaṃ paribhojanīyaṃ upaṭṭhāpetabbaṃ.**“Whoever returns first from almsround in the village should prepare the seats and set out a foot stool, a foot scraper, and water for washing the feet. He should clean the bowl for leftovers and set it out, and put out water for drinking and water for washing.*";
P_HTM[11070]="*Yo pacchā gāmato piṇḍāya paṭikkamati, sace hoti bhuttāvaseso, sace ākaṅkhati, bhuñjitabbaṃ.**Whoever returns last from almsround may eat whatever is leftover,*";
P_HTM[11071]="*No ce ākaṅkhati, appaharite vā chaḍḍetabbaṃ, appāṇake vā udake opilāpetabbaṃ.**or he should discard it where there are no cultivated plants or in water without life.*";
P_HTM[11072]="*Tena āsanaṃ uddharitabbaṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ pādakathalikaṃ paṭisāmetabbaṃ, avakkārapāti dhovitvā paṭisāmetabbā, pānīyaṃ paribhojanīyaṃ paṭisāmetabbaṃ, bhattaggaṃ sammajjitabbaṃ.**He should put away the seats and also the foot stool, the foot scraper, and the water for washing the feet. He should clean the bowl for leftovers and put it away, put away the water for drinking and the water for washing, and sweep the dining hall.*";
P_HTM[11073]="*Yo passati pānīyaghaṭaṃ vā paribhojanīyaghaṭaṃ vā vaccaghaṭaṃ vā rittaṃ tucchaṃ tena upaṭṭhāpetabbaṃ.**Whoever sees that the pot for drinking water, the pot for washing water, or the waterpot in the restroom is empty should fill it.*";
P_HTM[11074]="*Sacassa hoti avisayhaṃ, hatthavikārena dutiyaṃ āmantetvā hatthavilaṅghakena upaṭṭhāpetabbaṃ, na ca tappaccayā vācā bhinditabbā.**If he can’t do it by himself, he should call someone over by hand signal and they should fill it together. He should not speak because of that.*";
P_HTM[11075]="*Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, piṇḍacārikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ vattaṃ yathā piṇḍacārikehi bhikkhūhi sammā vattitabban”ti.**This is the proper conduct for alms-collectors.”*";
P_HTM[11076]="*7. Āraññikavattakathā**7. Discussion of the proper conduct for those staying in the wilderness*";
P_HTM[11077]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū araññe viharanti.**At that time there was a number of monks staying in the wilderness.*";
P_HTM[11078]="*Te neva pānīyaṃ upaṭṭhāpenti, na paribhojanīyaṃ upaṭṭhāpenti, na aggiṃ upaṭṭhāpenti, na araṇisahitaṃ upaṭṭhāpenti, na nakkhattapadāni jānanti, na disābhāgaṃ jānanti.**They did not set out water for drinking or water for washing; they did not light fires or provide upper and lower fire sticks; and they did not know the constellations or the cardinal directions.*";
P_HTM[11079]="*Corā tattha gantvā te bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—**Criminals went to that place and asked the monks,*";
P_HTM[11080]="*“atthi, bhante, pānīyan”ti?**“Sir, is there any water for drinking?” —*";
P_HTM[11081]="*“Natthāvuso”ti.**“No, there isn’t.” —*";
P_HTM[11082]="*“Atthi, bhante, paribhojanīyan”ti?**“Is there any water for washing?” —*";
P_HTM[11083]="*“Natthāvuso”ti.**“No.” —*";
P_HTM[11084]="*“Atthi, bhante, aggī”ti?**“Is there a fire?” —*";
P_HTM[11085]="*“Natthāvuso”ti.**“No.” —*";
P_HTM[11086]="*“Atthi, bhante, araṇisahitan”ti?**“Are there any upper and lower fire sticks?” —*";
P_HTM[11087]="*“Natthāvuso”ti.**“No.” —*";
P_HTM[11088]="*(…) “Kenajja, bhante, yuttan”ti?**“Which constellation is the moon in today?” —*";
P_HTM[11089]="*“Na kho mayaṃ, āvuso, jānāmā”ti.**“We don’t know.” —*";
P_HTM[11090]="*“Katamāyaṃ, bhante, disā”ti?**“Which direction is this?” —*";
P_HTM[11091]="*“Na kho mayaṃ, āvuso, jānāmā”ti.**“We don’t know.”*";
P_HTM[11092]="*Atha kho te corā—**Thinking,*";
P_HTM[11093]="*“nevimesaṃ pānīyaṃ atthi, na paribhojanīyaṃ atthi, na aggi atthi, na araṇisahitaṃ atthi, na nakkhattapadāni jānanti, na disābhāgaṃ jānanti;* **";
P_HTM[11094]="*corā ime, nayime bhikkhū”ti—**“They are criminals, not monks,”*";
P_HTM[11095]="*ākoṭetvā pakkamiṃsu.**they beat them up and left.*";
P_HTM[11096]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**The monks told other monks what had happened*";
P_HTM[11097]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**and they in turn told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[11098]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[11099]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, āraññikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ vattaṃ paññapessāmi yathā āraññikehi bhikkhūhi sammā vattitabbaṃ.**“Well then, I will lay down the proper conduct for monks staying in the wilderness.*";
P_HTM[11100]="*Āraññikena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā kālasseva uṭṭhāya pattaṃ thavikāya pakkhipitvā aṃse ālaggetvā cīvaraṃ khandhe karitvā upāhanā ārohitvā dārubhaṇḍaṃ mattikābhaṇḍaṃ paṭisāmetvā dvāravātapānaṃ thaketvā senāsanā otaritabbaṃ—**After getting up early in the morning, a monk who is staying in the wilderness should put his bowl in its bag, hang it from his shoulder, put his robe over his shoulders, put on his sandals, put the wooden and ceramic goods in order, close the door and windows, and descend from his dwelling.*";
P_HTM[11101]="*idāni gāmaṃ pavisissāmīti.**When he is about to enter the village,*";
P_HTM[11102]="*Upāhanā omuñcitvā nīcaṃ katvā papphoṭetvā thavikāya pakkhipitvā aṃse ālaggetvā timaṇḍalaṃ paṭicchādentena parimaṇḍalaṃ nivāsetvā kāyabandhanaṃ bandhitvā saguṇaṃ katvā saṅghāṭiyo pārupitvā gaṇṭhikaṃ paṭimuñcitvā dhovitvā pattaṃ gahetvā sādhukaṃ ataramānena gāmo pavisitabbo.**he should remove his sandals, hold them low and knock them together, before putting them in a bag, which he should hang from his shoulder. He should put on his sarong evenly all around, covering the navel and the knees. He should put on a belt. Putting the upper robes together, overlapping each other edge-to-edge, he should put them on and fasten the toggle. He should wash his bowl, bring it along, and enter the village carefully and without hurry.*";
P_HTM[11103]="*Suppaṭicchannena antaraghare gantabbaṃ …pe…**He should be well-covered when walking in inhabited areas; he should be well-restrained when walking in inhabited areas; he should walk with lowered eyes in inhabited areas; he should not walk with his robe lifted up in inhabited areas; he should not laugh loudly when walking in inhabited areas; he should not be noisy when walking in inhabited areas; he should not sway his body when walking in inhabited areas; he should not swing his arms when walking in inhabited areas; he should not sway his head when walking in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11104]="*na khambhakatena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not walk with arms akimbo in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11105]="*Na oguṇṭhitena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not walk with his head covered in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11106]="*Na ukkuṭikāya antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not squat on his heels when walking in inhabited areas.*";
P_HTM[11107]="*Nivesanaṃ pavisantena sallakkhetabbaṃ—**When entering a house,*";
P_HTM[11108]="*‘iminā pavisissāmi, iminā nikkhamissāmī’ti.**he should be attentive to where to enter and where to leave.*";
P_HTM[11109]="*Nātisahasā pavisitabbaṃ.**He should not enter*";
P_HTM[11110]="*Nātisahasā nikkhamitabbaṃ.**or leave too hastily;*";
P_HTM[11111]="*Nātidūre ṭhātabbaṃ.**he should not stand too far away*";
P_HTM[11112]="*Nāccāsanne ṭhātabbaṃ.**or too close;*";
P_HTM[11113]="*Nāticiraṃ ṭhātabbaṃ.**he should not wait too long*";
P_HTM[11114]="*Nātilahuṃ nivattitabbaṃ.**or leave too soon.*";
P_HTM[11115]="*Ṭhitakena sallakkhetabbaṃ—**While waiting,*";
P_HTM[11116]="*‘bhikkhaṃ dātukāmā vā adātukāmā vā’ti.**he should be attentive to whether they wish to give alms or not.*";
P_HTM[11117]="*Sace kammaṃ vā nikkhipati, āsanā vā vuṭṭhāti, kaṭacchuṃ vā parāmasati, bhājanaṃ vā parāmasati, ṭhapeti vā—**If they put down their work, get up from their seat, take hold of a serving spoon or a vessel, or they tell him to wait,*";
P_HTM[11118]="*dātukāmassāti ṭhātabbaṃ.**then he should assume they wish to give, and he should wait.*";
P_HTM[11119]="*Bhikkhāya diyyamānāya vāmena hatthena saṅghāṭiṃ uccāretvā dakkhiṇena hatthena pattaṃ paṇāmetvā ubhohi hatthehi pattaṃ paṭiggahetvā bhikkhā paṭiggahetabbā.**When they give him almsfood, he should lift up his upper robe with his left hand, stretch out his bowl with his right hand, and receive the alms while holding the bowl with both hands.*";
P_HTM[11120]="*Na ca bhikkhādāyikāya mukhaṃ ulloketabbaṃ.**He should not look the donor in the face.*";
P_HTM[11121]="*Sallakkhetabbaṃ—**He should be attentive*";
P_HTM[11122]="*‘sūpaṃ dātukāmā vā adātukāmā vā’ti.**to whether they wish to give curry or not.*";
P_HTM[11123]="*Sace kaṭacchuṃ vā parāmasati, bhājanaṃ vā parāmasati, ṭhapeti vā—**If they take hold of a serving spoon or a vessel, or they tell him to wait,*";
P_HTM[11124]="*dātukāmassāti ṭhātabbaṃ.**then he should assume they wish to give, and he should wait.*";
P_HTM[11125]="*Bhikkhāya dinnāya saṅghāṭiyā pattaṃ paṭicchādetvā sādhukaṃ ataramānena nivattitabbaṃ.**When they have given alms, he should cover the bowl with his upper robe, and return carefully and without hurry.*";
P_HTM[11126]="*Suppaṭicchannena antaraghare gantabbaṃ …pe…**He should be well-covered when walking in inhabited areas; he should be well-restrained when walking in inhabited areas; he should walk with lowered eyes in inhabited areas; he should not walk with his robe lifted up in inhabited areas; he should not laugh loudly when walking in inhabited areas; he should not be noisy when walking in inhabited areas; he should not sway his body when walking in inhabited areas; he should not swing his arms when walking in inhabited areas; he should not sway his head when walking in inhabited areas; he should not walk with arms akimbo in inhabited; he should not walk with his head covered in inhabited areas;*";
P_HTM[11127]="*na ukkuṭikāya antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**he should not squat on his heels when walking in inhabited areas.*";
P_HTM[11128]="*Gāmato nikkhamitvā pattaṃ thavikāya pakkhipitvā aṃse ālaggetvā cīvaraṃ saṅgharitvā sīse karitvā upāhanā ārohitvā gantabbaṃ.**When he has left the village, he should put his bowl in its bag and hang it from his shoulder, fold up his robe and put it on his head, and put on his sandals and go.*";
P_HTM[11129]="*Āraññikena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā pānīyaṃ upaṭṭhāpetabbaṃ, paribhojanīyaṃ upaṭṭhāpetabbaṃ, aggi upaṭṭhāpetabbo, araṇisahitaṃ upaṭṭhāpetabbaṃ, kattaradaṇḍo upaṭṭhāpetabbo, nakkhattapadāni uggahetabbāni—**A monk who is staying in the wilderness should set out water for drinking and water for washing; he should light a fire and provide upper and lower fire sticks; he should provide a walking stick; and he should learn the constellations—*";
P_HTM[11130]="*sakalāni vā ekadesāni vā, disākusalena bhavitabbaṃ.**all of them or those in one direction—and become skilled in the cardinal directions.*";
P_HTM[11131]="*Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, āraññikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ vattaṃ yathā āraññikehi bhikkhūhi sammā vattitabban”ti.**This is the proper conduct for those staying in the wilderness.”*";
P_HTM[11132]="*8. Senāsanavattakathā**8. Discussion of the proper conduct in regard to dwellings*";
P_HTM[11133]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū ajjhokāse cīvarakammaṃ karonti.**On one occasion when a number of monks were making robes outside,*";
P_HTM[11134]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū paṭivāte aṅgaṇe senāsanaṃ papphoṭesuṃ.**the monks from the group of six were beating furniture in an open space upwind from them.*";
P_HTM[11135]="*Bhikkhū rajena okiriṃsu.**The robe-making monks became dusty.*";
P_HTM[11136]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11137]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū paṭivāte aṅgaṇe senāsanaṃ papphoṭessanti.**“How can the monks from the group of six do this?”*";
P_HTM[11138]="*Bhikkhū rajena okiriṃsū”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11139]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[11140]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū paṭivāte aṅgaṇe senāsanaṃ papphoṭenti, bhikkhū rajena okiriṃsū”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the monks from the group of six did this?”*";
P_HTM[11141]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[11142]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[11143]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[11144]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ senāsanavattaṃ paññapessāmi yathā bhikkhūhi senāsane sammā vattitabbaṃ.**“Well then, I will lay down the proper conduct in regard to dwellings.*";
P_HTM[11145]="*Yasmiṃ vihāre viharati, sace so vihāro uklāpo hoti, sace ussahati, sodhetabbo.**If the dwelling he is staying in is dirty, a monk should clean it if he is able.*";
P_HTM[11146]="*Vihāraṃ sodhentena paṭhamaṃ pattacīvaraṃ nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ;**When he is cleaning the dwelling, he should first take out the bowl and robe and put them aside.*";
P_HTM[11147]="*nisīdanapaccattharaṇaṃ nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ;**He should take out the sitting mat and the sheet and put them aside.*";
P_HTM[11148]="*bhisibibbohanaṃ nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ;**He should take out the mattress and the pillow and put them aside.*";
P_HTM[11149]="*mañco nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena, asaṅghaṭṭentena kavāṭapiṭṭhaṃ, nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbo;**Holding the bed low, he should carefully take it out without scratching it or knocking it against the door or the door frame, and he should put it aside.*";
P_HTM[11150]="*pīṭhaṃ nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena, asaṅghaṭṭentena kavāṭapiṭṭhaṃ, nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ;**Holding the bench low, he should carefully take it out without scratching it or knocking it against the door or the door frame, and he should put it aside.*";
P_HTM[11151]="*mañcapaṭipādakā nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbā;**He should take out the bed supports and put them aside.*";
P_HTM[11152]="*kheḷamallako nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbo;**He should take out the spittoon and put it aside.*";
P_HTM[11153]="*apassenaphalakaṃ nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ;**He should take out the leaning board and put it aside.*";
P_HTM[11154]="*bhummattharaṇaṃ yathāpaññattaṃ sallakkhetvā nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ.**After taking note of its position, he should take out the floor cover and put it aside.*";
P_HTM[11155]="*Sace vihāre santānakaṃ hoti, ullokā paṭhamaṃ ohāretabbaṃ, ālokasandhikaṇṇabhāgā pamajjitabbā.**If the dwelling has cobwebs, he should first remove them from the ceiling cloth, and he should then wipe the windows and the corners of the room.*";
P_HTM[11156]="*Sace gerukaparikammakatā bhitti kaṇṇakitā hoti, coḷakaṃ temetvā pīḷetvā pamajjitabbā.**If the walls have been treated with red ocher and they’re moldy, he should moisten a cloth, wring it out, and wipe the walls.*";
P_HTM[11157]="*Sace kāḷavaṇṇakatā bhūmi kaṇṇakitā hoti, coḷakaṃ temetvā pīḷetvā pamajjitabbā.**If the floor has been treated with a black finish and it’s moldy, he should moisten a cloth, wring it out, and wipe the floor.*";
P_HTM[11158]="*Sace akatā hoti bhūmi, udakena paripphositvā paripphositvā sammajjitabbā—**If the floor is untreated, he should sprinkle it with water and then sweep it,*";
P_HTM[11159]="*mā vihāro rajena uhaññīti.**while trying to avoid stirring up dust.*";
P_HTM[11160]="*Saṅkāraṃ vicinitvā ekamantaṃ chaḍḍetabbaṃ.**He should look out for any trash and discard it.*";
P_HTM[11161]="*Na bhikkhusāmantā senāsanaṃ papphoṭetabbaṃ.**He should not beat the furniture near other monks,*";
P_HTM[11162]="*Na vihārasāmantā senāsanaṃ papphoṭetabbaṃ.**near other dwellings,*";
P_HTM[11163]="*Na pānīyasāmantā senāsanaṃ papphoṭetabbaṃ.**near water for drinking,*";
P_HTM[11164]="*Na paribhojanīyasāmantā senāsanaṃ papphoṭetabbaṃ.**or near water for washing.*";
P_HTM[11165]="*Na paṭivāte aṅgaṇe senāsanaṃ papphoṭetabbaṃ.**He should not beat the furniture in an open area upwind from these things,*";
P_HTM[11166]="*Adhovāte senāsanaṃ papphoṭetabbaṃ.**but downwind from them.*";
P_HTM[11167]="*Bhummattharaṇaṃ ekamantaṃ otāpetvā sodhetvā papphoṭetvā atiharitvā yathāpaññattaṃ paññapetabbaṃ.**He should sun the floor cover, clean it, beat it, bring it back inside, and put it back as before.*";
P_HTM[11168]="*Mañcapaṭipādakā ekamantaṃ otāpetvā pamajjitvā atiharitvā yathāṭhāne ṭhapetabbā.**He should sun the bed supports, wipe them, bring them back inside, and put them back where they were.*";
P_HTM[11169]="*Mañco ekamantaṃ otāpetvā sodhetvā papphoṭetvā nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena, asaṅghaṭṭentena kavāṭapiṭṭhaṃ, atiharitvā yathāpaññattaṃ paññapetabbo.**He should sun the bed, clean it, and beat it. Holding it low, he should carefully bring it back inside without scratching it or knocking it against the door or the door frame, and he should put it back as before.*";
P_HTM[11170]="*Pīṭhaṃ ekamantaṃ otāpetvā sodhetvā papphoṭetvā nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena, asaṅghaṭṭentena kavāṭapiṭṭhaṃ, atiharitvā yathāpaññattaṃ paññapetabbaṃ.**He should sun the bench, clean it, and beat it. Holding it low, he should carefully bring it back inside without scratching it or knocking it against the door or the door frame, and he should put it back as before.*";
P_HTM[11171]="*Bhisibibbohanaṃ ekamantaṃ otāpetvā sodhetvā papphoṭetvā atiharitvā yathāpaññattaṃ paññapetabbaṃ.**He should sun the mattress and the pillow, clean them, beat them, bring them back inside, and put them back as before.*";
P_HTM[11172]="*Nisīdanapaccattharaṇaṃ ekamantaṃ otāpetvā sodhetvā papphoṭetvā atiharitvā yathāpaññattaṃ paññapetabbaṃ.**He should sun the sitting mat and the sheet, clean them, beat them, bring them back inside, and put them back as before.*";
P_HTM[11173]="*Kheḷamallako ekamantaṃ otāpetvā pamajjitvā atiharitvā yathāṭhāne ṭhapetabbo.**He should sun the spittoon, wipe it, bring it back inside, and put it back where it was.*";
P_HTM[11174]="*Apassenaphalakaṃ ekamantaṃ otāpetvā pamajjitvā atiharitvā yathāṭhāne ṭhapetabbaṃ.**He should sun the leaning board, wipe it, bring it back inside, and put it back where it was.*";
P_HTM[11175]="*Pattacīvaraṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ.**He should put away the bowl and robe.*";
P_HTM[11176]="*Pattaṃ nikkhipantena ekena hatthena pattaṃ gahetvā ekena hatthena heṭṭhāmañcaṃ vā heṭṭhāpīṭhaṃ vā parāmasitvā patto nikkhipitabbo.**When putting away the bowl, he should hold the bowl in one hand, feel under the bed or the bench with the other, and then put it away.*";
P_HTM[11177]="*Na ca anantarahitāya bhūmiyā patto nikkhipitabbo.**He shouldn’t put the bowl away on the bare floor.*";
P_HTM[11178]="*Cīvaraṃ nikkhipantena ekena hatthena cīvaraṃ gahetvā ekena hatthena cīvaravaṃsaṃ vā cīvararajjuṃ vā pamajjitvā pārato antaṃ orato bhogaṃ katvā cīvaraṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ.**When putting away the robe, he should hold the robe in one hand, wipe the bamboo robe rack or the clothesline with the other, and then put it away by folding the robe over it, making the ends face the wall and the fold face out.*";
P_HTM[11179]="*Sace puratthimā sarajā vātā vāyanti, puratthimā vātapānā thaketabbā.**If dusty winds are blowing from the east, he should close the windows on the eastern side.*";
P_HTM[11180]="*Sace pacchimā sarajā vātā vāyanti, pacchimā vātapānā thaketabbā.**If dusty winds are blowing from the west, he should close the windows on the western side.*";
P_HTM[11181]="*Sace uttarā sarajā vātā vāyanti uttarā vātapānā thaketabbā.**If dusty winds are blowing from the north, he should close the windows on the northern side.*";
P_HTM[11182]="*Sace dakkhiṇā sarajā vātā vāyanti, dakkhiṇā vātapānā thaketabbā.**If dusty winds are blowing from the south, he should close the windows on the southern side.*";
P_HTM[11183]="*Sace sītakālo hoti, divā vātapānā vivaritabbā, rattiṃ thaketabbā.**If the weather is cold, he should open the windows during the day and close them at night.*";
P_HTM[11184]="*Sace uṇhakālo hoti, divā vātapānā thaketabbā, rattiṃ vivaritabbā.**If the weather is hot, he should close the windows during the day and open them at night.*";
P_HTM[11185]="*Sace pariveṇaṃ uklāpaṃ hoti, pariveṇaṃ sammajjitabbaṃ.**If the precincts are dirty, he should sweep them.*";
P_HTM[11186]="*Sace koṭṭhako uklāpo hoti, koṭṭhako sammajjitabbo.**If the gateway is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11187]="*Sace upaṭṭhānasālā uklāpā hoti, upaṭṭhānasālā sammajjitabbā.**If the assembly hall is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11188]="*Sace aggisālā uklāpā hoti, aggisālā sammajjitabbā.**If the water-boiling shed is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11189]="*Sace vaccakuṭi uklāpā hoti, vaccakuṭi sammajjitabbā.**If the restroom is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11190]="*Sace pānīyaṃ na hoti, pānīyaṃ upaṭṭhāpetabbaṃ.**If there is no water for drinking, he should get some.*";
P_HTM[11191]="*Sace paribhojanīyaṃ na hoti, paribhojanīyaṃ upaṭṭhāpetabbaṃ.**If there is no water for washing, he should get some.*";
P_HTM[11192]="*Sace ācamanakumbhiyā udakaṃ na hoti, ācamanakumbhiyā udakaṃ āsiñcitabbaṃ.**If there is no water in the rinsing pot, he should fill it.*";
P_HTM[11193]="*Sace vuḍḍhena saddhiṃ ekavihāre viharati, na vuḍḍhaṃ anāpucchā uddeso dātabbo, na paripucchā dātabbā, na sajjhāyo kātabbo, na dhammo bhāsitabbo, na padīpo kātabbo, na padīpo vijjhāpetabbo, na vātapānā vivaritabbā, na vātapānā thaketabbā.**If he is staying in the same dwelling as a more senior monk, he should not do any of the following without asking him for permission: recite, question, rehearse, teach, turn a lamp on or off, or open or close a window.*";
P_HTM[11194]="*Sace vuḍḍhena saddhiṃ ekacaṅkame caṅkamati, yena vuḍḍho tena parivattitabbaṃ, na ca vuḍḍho saṅghāṭikaṇṇena ghaṭṭetabbo.**If he is doing walking meditation on the same walking path as a more senior monk, he should walk behind him, but he should not hit him with the corners of his robe.*";
P_HTM[11195]="*Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ senāsanavattaṃ yathā bhikkhūhi senāsane sammā vattitabban”ti.**This is the proper conduct in regard to dwellings.”*";
P_HTM[11196]="*9. Jantāgharavattakathā**9. Discussion of the proper conduct in regard to saunas*";
P_HTM[11197]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū jantāghare therehi bhikkhūhi nivāriyamānā anādariyaṃ paṭicca pahūtaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ āropetvā aggiṃ datvā dvāraṃ thaketvā dvāre nisīdanti.**On one occasion the monks from the group of six were kept out of the sauna by the senior monks. Then, out of disrespect, they stacked up much firewood, lit it, closed the door, and sat down against it.*";
P_HTM[11198]="*Bhikkhū uṇhābhitattā dvāraṃ alabhamānā mucchitā papatanti.**The monks overheated, but being unable to open the door, they fainted and collapsed.*";
P_HTM[11199]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11200]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū jantāghare therehi bhikkhūhi nivāriyamānā anādariyaṃ paṭicca pahūtaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ āropetvā aggiṃ datvā dvāraṃ thaketvā dvāre nisīdissanti.**“How can the monks from the group of six do this?”*";
P_HTM[11201]="*Bhikkhū uṇhābhitattā dvāraṃ alabhamānā mucchitā papatantī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[11202]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[11203]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū jantāghare therehi bhikkhūhi nivāriyamānā anādariyaṃ paṭicca pahūtaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ āropetvā aggiṃ datvā dvāraṃ thaketvā dvāre nisīdanti;**“Is it true, monks, that the monks from the group of six did this?”*";
P_HTM[11204]="*bhikkhū uṇhābhitattā dvāraṃ alabhamānā mucchitā papatantī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[11205]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[11206]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[11207]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[11208]="*“na, bhikkhave, jantāghare therena bhikkhunā nivāriyamānena anādariyaṃ paṭicca pahūtaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ āropetvā aggi dātabbo.**“If you’re kept out of a sauna by senior monks, you should not, out of disrespect, stack up much firewood and light it.*";
P_HTM[11209]="*Yo dadeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11210]="*Na, bhikkhave, dvāraṃ thaketvā dvāre nisīditabbaṃ.**And you should not close the door and sit down against it.*";
P_HTM[11211]="*Yo nisīdeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11212]="*Tena hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ jantāgharavattaṃ paññapessāmi yathā bhikkhūhi jantāghare sammā vattitabbaṃ.**Well then, I will lay down the proper conduct in regard to saunas.*";
P_HTM[11213]="*Yo paṭhamaṃ jantāgharaṃ gacchati, sace chārikā ussannā hoti, chārikā chaḍḍetabbā.**The monk who goes first to the sauna should discard the ashes if they are building up.*";
P_HTM[11214]="*Sace jantāgharaṃ uklāpaṃ hoti, jantāgharaṃ sammajjitabbaṃ.**If the sauna is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11215]="*Sace paribhaṇḍaṃ uklāpaṃ hoti, paribhaṇḍaṃ sammajjitabbaṃ.**If the area immediately outside the sauna is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11216]="*Sace pariveṇaṃ uklāpaṃ hoti, pariveṇaṃ sammajjitabbaṃ.**If the precincts are dirty, he should sweep them.*";
P_HTM[11217]="*Sace koṭṭhako uklāpo hoti, koṭṭhako sammajjitabbo.**If the gateway is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11218]="*Sace jantāgharasālā uklāpā hoti, jantāgharasālā sammajjitabbā.**If the sauna shed is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11219]="*Cuṇṇaṃ sannetabbaṃ, mattikā temetabbā, udakadoṇikāya udakaṃ āsiñcitabbaṃ.**He should knead bath powder, moisten the clay, and fill the water trough with water.*";
P_HTM[11220]="*Jantāgharaṃ pavisantena mattikāya mukhaṃ makkhetvā purato ca pacchato ca paṭicchādetvā jantāgharaṃ pavisitabbaṃ.**When entering the sauna, he should smear his face with clay, cover himself front and back, and then enter.*";
P_HTM[11221]="*Na there bhikkhū anupakhajja nisīditabbaṃ.**He shouldn’t sit encroaching on the senior monks,*";
P_HTM[11222]="*Na navā bhikkhū āsanena paṭibāhitabbā.**and he shouldn’t block the junior monks from getting a seat.*";
P_HTM[11223]="*Sace ussahati, jantāghare therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ parikammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**If he is able, he should do services for the senior monks in the sauna.*";
P_HTM[11224]="*Jantāgharā nikkhamantena jantāgharapīṭhaṃ ādāya purato ca pacchato ca paṭicchādetvā jantāgharā nikkhamitabbaṃ.**When leaving the sauna, he should take the sauna stool, cover himself front and back, and then leave.*";
P_HTM[11225]="*Sace ussahati, udakepi therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ parikammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**If he is able, he should also do services for the senior monks in the water.*";
P_HTM[11226]="*Na therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ puratopi nahāyitabbaṃ, na uparitopi nahāyitabbaṃ.**He should not bathe in front of the senior monks or upstream from them.*";
P_HTM[11227]="*Nahātena uttarantena otarantānaṃ maggo dātabbo.**When he is coming out of the water after bathing, he should give way to those who are entering the water.*";
P_HTM[11228]="*Yo pacchā jantāgharā nikkhamati, sace jantāgharaṃ cikkhallaṃ hoti, dhovitabbaṃ.**If the sauna is muddy, the last monk to leave it should wash it.*";
P_HTM[11229]="*Mattikādoṇikaṃ dhovitvā jantāgharapīṭhaṃ paṭisāmetvā aggiṃ vijjhāpetvā dvāraṃ thaketvā pakkamitabbaṃ.**He should wash the clay trough, put away the sauna stool, extinguish the fire, close the door, and then leave.*";
P_HTM[11230]="*Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ jantāgharavattaṃ yathā bhikkhūhi jantāghare sammā vattitabban”ti.**This is the proper conduct in regard to saunas.”*";
P_HTM[11231]="*10. Vaccakuṭivattakathā**10. Discussion of the proper conduct in regard to restrooms*";
P_HTM[11232]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu brāhmaṇajātiko vaccaṃ katvā na icchati ācametuṃ—**At that time a monk who had been born as a brahmin did not want to rinse after defecating, thinking,*";
P_HTM[11233]="*“ko imaṃ vasalaṃ duggandhaṃ āmasissatī”ti.**“Who would touch this foul, stinking stuff?”*";
P_HTM[11234]="*Tassa vaccamagge kimi saṇṭhāti.**As a result, a worm settled in his anus.*";
P_HTM[11235]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**He told the monks, who said,*";
P_HTM[11236]="*“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, āvuso, vaccaṃ katvā na ācamesī”ti?**“So you don’t rinse after defecating?”*";
P_HTM[11237]="*“Evamāvuso”ti.**“That’s right.”*";
P_HTM[11238]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[11239]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhu vaccaṃ katvā na ācamessatī”ti.**“How can a monk not rinse after defecating?”*";
P_HTM[11240]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[11241]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, vaccaṃ katvā na ācamesī”ti?**“Is it true, monk, that you don’t rinse after defecating?”*";
P_HTM[11242]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[11243]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after rebuking them …*";
P_HTM[11244]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[11245]="*“na, bhikkhave, vaccaṃ katvā sati udake nācametabbaṃ.**“When there is water available, you should rinse after defecating.*";
P_HTM[11246]="*Yo nācameyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you don’t, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[11247]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū vaccakuṭiyā yathāvuḍḍhaṃ vaccaṃ karonti.**At that time the monks used the restroom according to seniority.*";
P_HTM[11248]="*Navakā bhikkhū paṭhamataraṃ āgantvā vaccitā āgamenti.**Junior monks who had arrived before others had to wait to defecate.*";
P_HTM[11249]="*Te vaccaṃ sandhārentā mucchitā papatanti.**Holding it in, they fainted and collapsed.*";
P_HTM[11250]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[11251]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave …pe…**“Is it true, monks, that this is happening?”*";
P_HTM[11252]="*“saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” … and the Buddha addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[11253]="*“na, bhikkhave, vaccakuṭiyā yathāvuḍḍhaṃ vacco kātabbo.**“The restroom should not be used according to seniority.*";
P_HTM[11254]="*Yo kareyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11255]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, āgatapaṭipāṭiyā vaccaṃ kātun”ti.**You should use the restroom according to the order of arrival.”*";
P_HTM[11256]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū atisahasāpi vaccakuṭiṃ pavisanti, ubbhajitvāpi pavisanti, nitthunantāpi vaccaṃ karonti, dantakaṭṭhaṃ khādantāpi vaccaṃ karonti, bahiddhāpi vaccadoṇikāya vaccaṃ karonti, bahiddhāpi passāvadoṇikāya passāvaṃ karonti, passāvadoṇikāyapi kheḷaṃ karonti, pharusenapi kaṭṭhena avalekhanti, avalekhanakaṭṭhampi vaccakūpamhi pātenti, atisahasāpi nikkhamanti, ubbhajitvāpi nikkhamanti, capucapukārakampi ācamenti, ācamanasarāvakepi udakaṃ sesenti.**At that time the monks from the group of six entered the restroom too hastily, pulled up their robe before entering, groaned while defecating, cleaned their teeth while defecating, defecated outside the toilet, urinated outside the urinal, spat in the urinal, used coarse wiping sticks, threw the wiping sticks in the cesspit, left the restroom too hastily, came out with their robe still pulled up, made a chomping sound while rinsing, and they left water in the scoop for rinsing.*";
P_HTM[11257]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11258]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū atisahasāpi vaccakuṭiṃ pavisissanti, ubbhajitvāpi pavisissanti, nitthunantāpi vaccaṃ karissanti, dantakaṭṭhaṃ khādantāpi vaccaṃ karissanti, bahiddhāpi vaccadoṇikāya vaccaṃ karissanti, bahiddhāpi passāvadoṇikāya passāvaṃ karissanti, passāvadoṇikāyapi kheḷaṃ karissanti, pharusenapi kaṭṭhena avalekhissanti, avalekhanakaṭṭhampi vaccakūpamhi pātessanti, atisahasāpi nikkhamissanti, ubbhajitvāpi nikkhamissanti, capucapukārakampi ācamessanti, ācamanasarāvakepi udakaṃ sesessantī”ti.**“How can the monks from the group of six act like this?”*";
P_HTM[11259]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[11260]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave …pe…**“Is it true, monks, that the monks from the group of six act like this?”*";
P_HTM[11261]="*“saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[11262]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[11263]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[11264]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ vaccakuṭivattaṃ paññapessāmi yathā bhikkhūhi vaccakuṭiyā sammā vattitabbaṃ.**“Well then, I will lay down the proper conduct in regard to restrooms.*";
P_HTM[11265]="*Yo vaccakuṭiṃ gacchati tena bahi ṭhitena ukkāsitabbaṃ.**When a monk goes to the restroom, he should stand outside and clear his throat.*";
P_HTM[11266]="*Anto nisinnenapi ukkāsitabbaṃ.**Anyone sitting inside should also clear his throat.*";
P_HTM[11267]="*Cīvaravaṃse vā cīvararajjuyā vā cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā sādhukaṃ ataramānena vaccakuṭi pavisitabbā.**After hanging his robe from a bamboo robe rack or a clothesline, he should enter the restroom carefully and without hurry.*";
P_HTM[11268]="*Nātisahasā pavisitabbā.**He should not enter the restroom too hastily;*";
P_HTM[11269]="*Na ubbhajitvā pavisitabbā.**he should not pull up his robe before he has entered;*";
P_HTM[11270]="*Vaccapādukāya ṭhitena ubbhajitabbaṃ.**he should pull up his robe when he is standing on the foot-stands for defecating;*";
P_HTM[11271]="*Na nitthunantena vacco kātabbo.**he should not groan while defecating;*";
P_HTM[11272]="*Na dantakaṭṭhaṃ khādantena vacco kātabbo.**he should not clean his teeth while defecating;*";
P_HTM[11273]="*Na bahiddhā vaccadoṇikāya vacco kātabbo.**he should not defecate outside the toilet;*";
P_HTM[11274]="*Na bahiddhā passāvadoṇikāya passāvo kātabbo.**he should not urinate outside the urinal;*";
P_HTM[11275]="*Na passāvadoṇikāya kheḷo kātabbo.**he should not spit in the urinal;*";
P_HTM[11276]="*Na pharusena kaṭṭhena avalekhitabbaṃ.**he should not use coarse wiping sticks;*";
P_HTM[11277]="*Na avalekhanakaṭṭhaṃ vaccakūpamhi pātetabbaṃ.**he should not throw the wiping sticks in the cesspit;*";
P_HTM[11278]="*Vaccapādukāya ṭhitena paṭicchādetabbaṃ.**he should cover himself while still standing on the foot-stands for defecating;*";
P_HTM[11279]="*Nātisahasā nikkhamitabbaṃ.**he should not leave the restroom too hastily;*";
P_HTM[11280]="*Na ubbhajitvā nikkhamitabbaṃ.**he should not come out with his robe still pulled up;*";
P_HTM[11281]="*Ācamanapādukāya ṭhitena ubbhajitabbaṃ.**he should pull up his robe when standing on the foot-stands for rinsing;*";
P_HTM[11282]="*Na capucapukārakaṃ ācametabbaṃ.**he should not make a chomping sound while rinsing;*";
P_HTM[11283]="*Na ācamanasarāvake udakaṃ sesetabbaṃ.**he should not leave water in the scoop for rinsing;*";
P_HTM[11284]="*Ācamanapādukāya ṭhitena paṭicchādetabbaṃ.**he should cover himself while still standing on the foot-stands for rinsing.*";
P_HTM[11285]="*Sace vaccakuṭi uhatā hoti, dhovitabbā.**If the restroom is stained by feces, he should clean it.*";
P_HTM[11286]="*Sace avalekhanapidharo pūro hoti, avalekhanakaṭṭhaṃ chaḍḍetabbaṃ.**If the wiping-stick container is full, he should discard the wiping sticks.*";
P_HTM[11287]="*Sace vaccakuṭi uklāpā hoti, vaccakuṭi sammajjitabbā.**If the restroom is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11288]="*Sace paribhaṇḍaṃ uklāpaṃ hoti, paribhaṇḍaṃ sammajjitabbaṃ.**If the area immediately outside the restroom is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11289]="*Sace pariveṇaṃ uklāpaṃ hoti, pariveṇaṃ sammajjitabbaṃ.**If the precincts are dirty, he should sweep them.*";
P_HTM[11290]="*Sace koṭṭhako uklāpo hoti, koṭṭhako sammajjitabbo.**If the gateway is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11291]="*Sace ācamanakumbhiyā udakaṃ na hoti, ācamanakumbhiyā udakaṃ āsiñcitabbaṃ.**If there is no water in the pot for rinsing water, he should fill it.*";
P_HTM[11292]="*Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ vaccakuṭivattaṃ yathā bhikkhūhi vaccakuṭiyā sammā vattitabban”ti.**This is the proper conduct in regard to restrooms.”*";
P_HTM[11293]="*11. Upajjhāyavattakathā**11. Discussion of the proper conduct toward a preceptor*";
P_HTM[11294]="*Tena kho pana samayena saddhivihārikā upajjhāyesu na sammā vattanti.**At that time the students were not conducting themselves properly toward their preceptors.*";
P_HTM[11295]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11296]="*“kathañhi nāma saddhivihārikā upajjhāyesu na sammā vattissantī”ti.**“How can the students not conduct themselves properly toward their preceptors?”*";
P_HTM[11297]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[11298]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, saddhivihārikā upajjhāyesu na sammā vattantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the students are not conducting themselves properly toward their preceptors?”*";
P_HTM[11299]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[11300]="*vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[11301]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, saddhivihārikā upajjhāyesu na sammā vattissanti.**“How can they act like this?*";
P_HTM[11302]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …”*";
P_HTM[11303]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[11304]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[11305]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, saddhivihārikānaṃ upajjhāyesu vattaṃ paññapessāmi yathā saddhivihārikehi upajjhāyesu sammā vattitabbaṃ.**“Well then, I will lay down the proper conduct for a student toward his preceptor*";
P_HTM[11306]="*Saddhivihārikena, bhikkhave, upajjhāyamhi sammā vattitabbaṃ.**A student should conduct himself properly toward his preceptor.*";
P_HTM[11307]="*Tatrāyaṃ sammāvattanā—**This is the proper conduct:*";
P_HTM[11308]="*Kālasseva uṭṭhāya upāhanā omuñcitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā dantakaṭṭhaṃ dātabbaṃ, mukhodakaṃ dātabbaṃ, āsanaṃ paññapetabbaṃ.**Having gotten up at the appropriate time, the student should remove his sandals and put his upper robe over one shoulder. He should then give his preceptor a tooth cleaner and water for rinsing the mouth, and he should prepare a seat for him.*";
P_HTM[11309]="*Sace yāgu hoti, bhājanaṃ dhovitvā yāgu upanāmetabbā.**If there is rice porridge, he should wash a vessel and bring the rice porridge to his preceptor.*";
P_HTM[11310]="*Yāguṃ pītassa udakaṃ datvā bhājanaṃ paṭiggahetvā nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena dhovitvā paṭisāmetabbaṃ.**When the preceptor has drunk the rice porridge, the student should give him water and receive the vessel. Holding it low, he should wash it carefully without scratching it and then put it away.*";
P_HTM[11311]="*Upajjhāyamhi vuṭṭhite āsanaṃ uddharitabbaṃ.**When the preceptor has gotten up, the student should put away the seat.*";
P_HTM[11312]="*Sace so deso uklāpo hoti, so deso sammajjitabbo.**If the place is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11313]="*Sace upajjhāyo gāmaṃ pavisitukāmo hoti, nivāsanaṃ dātabbaṃ, paṭinivāsanaṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ, kāyabandhanaṃ dātabbaṃ, saguṇaṃ katvā saṅghāṭiyo dātabbā, dhovitvā patto sodako dātabbo.**If the preceptor wants to enter the village, the student should give him a sarong and receive the one he’s wearing in return. He should give him a belt. He should put the upper robes together, overlapping each other edge-to-edge, and then give them to him. He should wash his preceptor’s bowl and give it to him while wet.*";
P_HTM[11314]="*Sace upajjhāyo pacchāsamaṇaṃ ākaṅkhati, timaṇḍalaṃ paṭicchādentena parimaṇḍalaṃ nivāsetvā kāyabandhanaṃ bandhitvā saguṇaṃ katvā saṅghāṭiyo pārupitvā gaṇṭhikaṃ paṭimuñcitvā dhovitvā pattaṃ gahetvā upajjhāyassa pacchāsamaṇena hotabbaṃ.**If the preceptor wants an attendant, the student should put on his sarong evenly all around, covering the navel and the knees. He should put on a belt. Putting the upper robes together, overlapping each other edge-to-edge, he should put them on and fasten the toggle. He should wash his bowl, bring it along, and be his preceptor’s attendant.*";
P_HTM[11315]="*Nātidūre gantabbaṃ, nāccāsanne gantabbaṃ, pattapariyāpannaṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ.**He shouldn’t walk too far behind his preceptor or too close to him. He should receive the contents of his bowl.*";
P_HTM[11316]="*Na upajjhāyassa bhaṇamānassa antarantarā kathā opātetabbā.**He shouldn’t interrupt his preceptor when he’s speaking.*";
P_HTM[11317]="*Upajjhāyo āpattisāmantā bhaṇamāno nivāretabbo.**But if the preceptor’s speech is bordering on an offense, he should stop him.*";
P_HTM[11318]="*Nivattantena paṭhamataraṃ āgantvā āsanaṃ paññapetabbaṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ pādakathalikaṃ upanikkhipitabbaṃ, paccuggantvā pattacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ, paṭinivāsanaṃ dātabbaṃ, nivāsanaṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ.**When returning, the student should go first to prepare a seat and to set out a foot stool, a foot scraper, and water for washing the feet. He should go out to meet the preceptor and receive his bowl and robe. He should give him a sarong and receive the one he’s wearing in return.*";
P_HTM[11319]="*Sace cīvaraṃ sinnaṃ hoti, muhuttaṃ uṇhe otāpetabbaṃ, na ca uṇhe cīvaraṃ nidahitabbaṃ.**If the robe is moist, he should sun it for a short while, but he shouldn’t leave it in the heat.*";
P_HTM[11320]="*Cīvaraṃ saṅgharitabbaṃ.**He should fold the robe,*";
P_HTM[11321]="*Cīvaraṃ saṅgharantena caturaṅgulaṃ kaṇṇaṃ ussāretvā cīvaraṃ saṅgharitabbaṃ—**offsetting the edges by seven centimeters,*";
P_HTM[11322]="*mā majjhe bhaṅgo ahosīti.**so that the fold doesn’t become worn.*";
P_HTM[11323]="*Obhoge kāyabandhanaṃ kātabbaṃ.**He should place the belt in the fold.*";
P_HTM[11324]="*Sace piṇḍapāto hoti, upajjhāyo ca bhuñjitukāmo hoti, udakaṃ datvā piṇḍapāto upanāmetabbo.**If there is almsfood and his preceptor wants to eat, the student should give him water and then the almsfood.*";
P_HTM[11325]="*Upajjhāyo pānīyena pucchitabbo.**He should ask his preceptor if he wants water to drink.*";
P_HTM[11326]="*Bhuttāvissa udakaṃ datvā pattaṃ paṭiggahetvā nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena dhovitvā vodakaṃ katvā muhuttaṃ uṇhe otāpetabbo.**When the preceptor has eaten, the student should give him water and receive his bowl. Holding it low, he should wash it carefully without scratching it. He should then dry it and sun it for a short while,*";
P_HTM[11327]="*Na ca uṇhe patto nidahitabbo.**but he shouldn’t leave it in the heat.*";
P_HTM[11328]="*Pattacīvaraṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ.**The student should put away the robe and bowl.*";
P_HTM[11329]="*Pattaṃ nikkhipantena ekena hatthena pattaṃ gahetvā ekena hatthena heṭṭhāmañcaṃ vā heṭṭhāpīṭhaṃ vā parāmasitvā patto nikkhipitabbo.**When putting away the bowl, he should hold the bowl in one hand, feel under the bed or the bench with the other, and then put it away.*";
P_HTM[11330]="*Na ca anantarahitāya bhūmiyā patto nikkhipitabbo.**He shouldn’t put the bowl away on the bare floor.*";
P_HTM[11331]="*Cīvaraṃ nikkhipantena ekena hatthena cīvaraṃ gahetvā ekena hatthena cīvaravaṃsaṃ vā cīvararajjuṃ vā pamajjitvā pārato antaṃ orato bhogaṃ katvā cīvaraṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ.**When putting away the robe, he should hold the robe in one hand, wipe the bamboo robe rack or the clothesline with the other, and then put it away by folding the robe over it, making the ends face the wall and the fold face out.*";
P_HTM[11332]="*Upajjhāyamhi vuṭṭhite āsanaṃ uddharitabbaṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ pādakathalikaṃ paṭisāmetabbaṃ.**When the preceptor has gotten up, the student should put away the seat and also the foot stool, the foot scraper, and the water for washing the feet.*";
P_HTM[11333]="*Sace so deso uklāpo hoti, so deso sammajjitabbo.**If the place is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11334]="*Sace upajjhāyo nahāyitukāmo hoti, nahānaṃ paṭiyādetabbaṃ.**“If the preceptor wants to bathe, the student should prepare a bath.*";
P_HTM[11335]="*Sace sītena attho hoti, sītaṃ paṭiyādetabbaṃ.**If he wants a cold bath, he should prepare that;*";
P_HTM[11336]="*Sace uṇhena attho hoti, uṇhaṃ paṭiyādetabbaṃ.**if he wants a hot bath, he should prepare that.*";
P_HTM[11337]="*Sace upajjhāyo jantāgharaṃ pavisitukāmo hoti, cuṇṇaṃ sannetabbaṃ, mattikā temetabbā, jantāgharapīṭhaṃ ādāya upajjhāyassa piṭṭhito piṭṭhito gantvā jantāgharapīṭhaṃ datvā cīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ, cuṇṇaṃ dātabbaṃ, mattikā dātabbā.**If the preceptor wants to take a sauna, the student should knead bath powder, moisten the clay, take a sauna stool, and follow behind his preceptor. After giving the preceptor the sauna stool, receiving his robe, and putting it aside, he should give him the bath powder and the clay.*";
P_HTM[11338]="*Sace ussahati, jantāgharaṃ pavisitabbaṃ.**If he’s able, he should enter the sauna.*";
P_HTM[11339]="*Jantāgharaṃ pavisantena mattikāya mukhaṃ makkhetvā purato ca pacchato ca paṭicchādetvā jantāgharaṃ pavisitabbaṃ.**When entering the sauna, he should smear his face with clay, cover himself front and back, and then enter.*";
P_HTM[11340]="*Na there bhikkhū anupakhajja nisīditabbaṃ.**He shouldn’t sit encroaching on the senior monks,*";
P_HTM[11341]="*Na navā bhikkhū āsanena paṭibāhitabbā.**and he shouldn’t block the junior monks from getting a seat.*";
P_HTM[11342]="*Jantāghare upajjhāyassa parikammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**While in the sauna, he should do services for his preceptor.*";
P_HTM[11343]="*Jantāgharā nikkhamantena jantāgharapīṭhaṃ ādāya purato ca pacchato ca paṭicchādetvā jantāgharā nikkhamitabbaṃ.**When leaving the sauna, he should take the sauna stool, cover himself front and back, and then leave.*";
P_HTM[11344]="*Udakepi upajjhāyassa parikammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**He should also do services for his preceptor in the water.*";
P_HTM[11345]="*Nahātena paṭhamataraṃ uttaritvā attano gattaṃ vodakaṃ katvā nivāsetvā upajjhāyassa gattato udakaṃ pamajjitabbaṃ, nivāsanaṃ dātabbaṃ, saṅghāṭi dātabbā, jantāgharapīṭhaṃ ādāya paṭhamataraṃ āgantvā āsanaṃ paññapetabbaṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ pādakathalikaṃ upanikkhipitabbaṃ.**When he has bathed, he should be the first to come out. He should dry himself and put on his sarong. He should then wipe the water off his preceptor’s body, and he should give him his sarong and then his upper robe. Taking the sauna stool, he should be the first to return. He should prepare a seat, and also set out a foot stool, a foot scraper, and water for washing the feet.*";
P_HTM[11346]="*Upajjhāyo pānīyena pucchitabbo.**He should ask his preceptor if he wants water to drink.*";
P_HTM[11347]="*Sace uddisāpetukāmo hoti, uddisitabbo.**If the preceptor wants him to recite, he should do so.*";
P_HTM[11348]="*Sace paripucchitukāmo hoti, paripucchitabbo.**If the preceptor wants to question him, he should be questioned.*";
P_HTM[11349]="*Yasmiṃ vihāre upajjhāyo viharati, sace so vihāro uklāpo hoti, sace ussahati, sodhetabbo.**“If the dwelling where the preceptor is staying is dirty, the student should clean it if he’s able.*";
P_HTM[11350]="*Vihāraṃ sodhentena paṭhamaṃ pattacīvaraṃ nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ;**When he’s cleaning the dwelling, he should first take out the bowl and robe and put them aside.*";
P_HTM[11351]="*nisīdanapaccattharaṇaṃ nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ;**He should take out the sitting mat and the sheet and put them aside.*";
P_HTM[11352]="*bhisibibbohanaṃ nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ;**He should take out the mattress and the pillow and put them aside.*";
P_HTM[11353]="*mañco nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena, asaṅghaṭṭentena kavāṭapiṭṭhaṃ, nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbo;**Holding the bed low, he should carefully take it out without scratching it or knocking it against the door or the door frame, and he should put it aside.*";
P_HTM[11354]="*pīṭhaṃ nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena, asaṅghaṭṭentena kavāṭapiṭṭhaṃ, nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ;**Holding the bench low, he should carefully take it out without scratching it or knocking it against the door or the door frame, and he should put it aside.*";
P_HTM[11355]="*mañcapaṭipādakā nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbā;**He should take out the bed supports and put them aside.*";
P_HTM[11356]="*kheḷamallako nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbo;**He should take out the spittoon and put it aside.*";
P_HTM[11357]="*apassenaphalakaṃ nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ;**He should take out the leaning board and put it aside.*";
P_HTM[11358]="*bhūmattharaṇaṃ yathāpaññattaṃ sallakkhetvā nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ.**After taking note of its position, he should take out the floor cover and put it aside.*";
P_HTM[11359]="*Sace vihāre santānakaṃ hoti, ullokā paṭhamaṃ ohāretabbaṃ, ālokasandhikaṇṇabhāgā pamajjitabbā.**If the dwelling has cobwebs, he should first remove them from the ceiling cloth, and he should then wipe the windows and the corners of the room.*";
P_HTM[11360]="*Sace gerukaparikammakatā bhitti kaṇṇakitā hoti, coḷakaṃ temetvā pīḷetvā pamajjitabbā.**If the walls have been treated with red ocher and they’re moldy, he should moisten a cloth, wring it out, and wipe the walls.*";
P_HTM[11361]="*Sace kāḷavaṇṇakatā bhūmi kaṇṇakitā hoti, coḷakaṃ temetvā pīḷetvā pamajjitabbā.**If the floor has been treated with a black finish and it’s moldy, he should moisten a cloth, wring it out, and wipe the floor.*";
P_HTM[11362]="*Sace akatā hoti bhūmi, udakena paripphositvā paripphositvā sammajjitabbā—**If the floor is untreated, he should sprinkle it with water and then sweep it,*";
P_HTM[11363]="*mā vihāro rajena uhaññīti.**while trying to avoid stirring up dust.*";
P_HTM[11364]="*Saṅkāraṃ vicinitvā ekamantaṃ chaḍḍetabbaṃ.**He should look out for any trash and discard it.*";
P_HTM[11365]="*Bhūmattharaṇaṃ otāpetvā sodhetvā papphoṭetvā atiharitvā yathāpaññattaṃ paññapetabbaṃ.**He should sun the floor cover, clean it, beat it, bring it back inside, and put it back as before.*";
P_HTM[11366]="*Mañcapaṭipādakā otāpetvā pamajjitvā atiharitvā yathāṭhāne ṭhapetabbā.**He should sun the bed supports, wipe them, bring them back inside, and put them back where they were.*";
P_HTM[11367]="*Mañco otāpetvā sodhetvā papphoṭetvā nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena, asaṅghaṭṭentena kavāṭapiṭṭhaṃ, atiharitvā yathāpaññattaṃ paññapetabbo.**He should sun the bed, clean it, and beat it. Holding it low, he should carefully bring it back inside without scratching it or knocking it against the door or the door frame, and he should put it back as before.*";
P_HTM[11368]="*Pīṭhaṃ otāpetvā sodhetvā papphoṭetvā nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena, asaṅghaṭṭentena kavāṭapiṭṭhaṃ, atiharitvā yathāpaññattaṃ paññapetabbaṃ.**He should sun the bench, clean it, and beat it. Holding it low, he should carefully bring it back inside without scratching it or knocking it against the door or the door frame, and he should put it back as before.*";
P_HTM[11369]="*Bhisibibbohanaṃ otāpetvā sodhetvā papphoṭetvā atiharitvā yathāpaññattaṃ paññapetabbaṃ.**He should sun the mattress and the pillow, clean them, beat them, bring them back inside, and put them back as before.*";
P_HTM[11370]="*Nisīdanapaccattharaṇaṃ otāpetvā sodhetvā papphoṭetvā atiharitvā yathāpaññattaṃ paññapetabbaṃ.**He should sun the sitting mat and the sheet, clean them, beat them, bring them back inside, and put them back as before.*";
P_HTM[11371]="*Kheḷamallako otāpetvā pamajjitvā atiharitvā yathāṭhāne ṭhapetabbo.**He should sun the spittoon, wipe it, bring it back inside, and put it back where it was.*";
P_HTM[11372]="*Apassenaphalakaṃ otāpetvā pamajjitvā atiharitvā yathāṭhāne ṭhapetabbaṃ.**He should sun the leaning board, wipe it, bring it back inside, and put it back where it was.*";
P_HTM[11373]="*Pattacīvaraṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ.**He should put away the bowl and robe.*";
P_HTM[11374]="*Pattaṃ nikkhipantena ekena hatthena pattaṃ gahetvā ekena hatthena heṭṭhāmañcaṃ vā heṭṭhāpīṭhaṃ vā parāmasitvā patto nikkhipitabbo.**When putting away the bowl, he should hold the bowl in one hand, feel under the bed or the bench with the other, and then put it away.*";
P_HTM[11375]="*Na ca anantarahitāya bhūmiyā patto nikkhipitabbo.**He shouldn’t put the bowl away on the bare floor.*";
P_HTM[11376]="*Cīvaraṃ nikkhipantena ekena hatthena cīvaraṃ gahetvā ekena hatthena cīvaravaṃsaṃ vā cīvararajjuṃ vā pamajjitvā pārato antaṃ orato bhogaṃ katvā cīvaraṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ.**When putting away the robe, he should hold the robe in one hand, wipe the bamboo robe rack or the clothesline with the other, and then put it away by folding the robe over it, making the ends face the wall and the fold face out.*";
P_HTM[11377]="*Sace puratthimā sarajā vātā vāyanti, puratthimā vātapānā thaketabbā.**If dusty winds are blowing from the east, he should close the windows on the eastern side.*";
P_HTM[11378]="*Sace pacchimā sarajā vātā vāyanti, pacchimā vātapānā thaketabbā.**If dusty winds are blowing from the west, he should close the windows on the western side.*";
P_HTM[11379]="*Sace uttarā sarajā vātā vāyanti, uttarā vātapānā thaketabbā.**If dusty winds are blowing from the north, he should close the windows on the northern side.*";
P_HTM[11380]="*Sace dakkhiṇā sarajā vātā vāyanti, dakkhiṇā vātapānā thaketabbā.**If dusty winds are blowing from the south, he should close the windows on the southern side.*";
P_HTM[11381]="*Sace sītakālo hoti, divā vātapānā vivaritabbā, rattiṃ thaketabbā.**If the weather is cold, he should open the windows during the day and close them at night.*";
P_HTM[11382]="*Sace uṇhakālo hoti, divā vātapānā thaketabbā, rattiṃ vivaritabbā.**If the weather is hot, he should close the windows during the day and open them at night.*";
P_HTM[11383]="*Sace pariveṇaṃ uklāpaṃ hoti, pariveṇaṃ sammajjitabbaṃ.**If the precincts are dirty, he should sweep them.*";
P_HTM[11384]="*Sace koṭṭhako uklāpo hoti, koṭṭhako sammajjitabbo.**If the gateway is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11385]="*Sace upaṭṭhānasālā uklāpā hoti, upaṭṭhānasālā sammajjitabbā.**If the assembly hall is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11386]="*Sace aggisālā uklāpā hoti, aggisālā sammajjitabbā.**If the water-boiling shed is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11387]="*Sace vaccakuṭi uklāpā hoti, vaccakuṭi sammajjitabbā.**If the restroom is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11388]="*Sace pānīyaṃ na hoti, pānīyaṃ upaṭṭhāpetabbaṃ.**If there is no water for drinking, he should get some.*";
P_HTM[11389]="*Sace paribhojanīyaṃ na hoti, paribhojanīyaṃ upaṭṭhāpetabbaṃ.**If there is no water for washing, he should get some.*";
P_HTM[11390]="*Sace ācamanakumbhiyā udakaṃ na hoti, ācamanakumbhiyā udakaṃ āsiñcitabbaṃ.**If there is no water in the rinsing pot, he should fill it.*";
P_HTM[11391]="*Sace upajjhāyassa anabhirati uppannā hoti, saddhivihārikena vūpakāsetabbo, vūpakāsāpetabbo, dhammakathā vāssa kātabbā.**“If the preceptor becomes discontent with the spiritual life, the student should send him away or have him sent away, or he should give him a teaching.*";
P_HTM[11392]="*Sace upajjhāyassa kukkuccaṃ uppannaṃ hoti, saddhivihārikena vinodetabbaṃ, vinodāpetabbaṃ, dhammakathā vāssa kātabbā.**If the preceptor becomes anxious, the student should dispel it or have it dispelled, or he should give him a teaching.*";
P_HTM[11393]="*Sace upajjhāyassa diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ hoti, saddhivihārikena vivecetabbaṃ, vivecāpetabbaṃ, dhammakathā vāssa kātabbā.**If the preceptor has a wrong view, the student should make him give it up or have someone else do it, or he should give him a teaching.*";
P_HTM[11394]="*Sace upajjhāyo garudhammaṃ ajjhāpanno hoti parivāsāraho, saddhivihārikena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**If the preceptor has committed a heavy offense and deserves probation,*";
P_HTM[11395]="*kinti nu kho saṅgho upajjhāyassa parivāsaṃ dadeyyāti.**the student should try to get the Sangha to give it to him.*";
P_HTM[11396]="*Sace upajjhāyo mūlāyapaṭikassanāraho hoti, saddhivihārikena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**If the preceptor has committed a heavy offense and deserves to be sent back to the beginning,*";
P_HTM[11397]="*kinti nu kho saṅgho upajjhāyaṃ mūlāya paṭikasseyyāti.**the student should try to get the Sangha to do it.*";
P_HTM[11398]="*Sace upajjhāyo mānattāraho hoti, saddhivihārikena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**If the preceptor has committed a heavy offense and deserves the trial period,*";
P_HTM[11399]="*kinti nu kho saṅgho upajjhāyassa mānattaṃ dadeyyāti.**the student should try to get the Sangha to give it to him.*";
P_HTM[11400]="*Sace upajjhāyo abbhānāraho hoti, saddhivihārikena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**If the preceptor has committed a heavy offense and deserves rehabilitation,*";
P_HTM[11401]="*kinti nu kho saṅgho upajjhāyaṃ abbheyyāti.**the student should try to get the Sangha to give it to him.*";
P_HTM[11402]="*Sace saṅgho upajjhāyassa kammaṃ kattukāmo hoti, tajjanīyaṃ vā niyassaṃ vā pabbājanīyaṃ vā paṭisāraṇīyaṃ vā ukkhepanīyaṃ vā, saddhivihārikena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**If the Sangha wants to do a legal procedure against his preceptor—whether a procedure of condemnation, demotion, banishment, reconciliation, or ejection—*";
P_HTM[11403]="*kinti nu kho saṅgho upajjhāyassa kammaṃ na kareyya, lahukāya vā pariṇāmeyyāti.**the student should make an effort to stop it or to reduce the penalty.*";
P_HTM[11404]="*Kataṃ vā panassa hoti saṅghena kammaṃ, tajjanīyaṃ vā niyassaṃ vā pabbājanīyaṃ vā paṭisāraṇīyaṃ vā ukkhepanīyaṃ vā, saddhivihārikena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**But if the Sangha has already done a legal procedure against his preceptor—whether a procedure of condemnation, demotion, banishment, reconciliation, or ejection—*";
P_HTM[11405]="*kinti nu kho upajjhāyo sammā vatteyya, lomaṃ pāteyya, netthāraṃ vatteyya, saṅgho taṃ kammaṃ paṭippassambheyyāti.**the student should help the preceptor conduct himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and try to get the Sangha to lift that procedure.*";
P_HTM[11406]="*Sace upajjhāyassa cīvaraṃ dhovitabbaṃ hoti, saddhivihārikena dhovitabbaṃ, ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—**“If the preceptor’s robe needs washing, the student should do it himself,*";
P_HTM[11407]="*kinti nu kho upajjhāyassa cīvaraṃ dhoviyethāti.**or he should make an effort to get it done.*";
P_HTM[11408]="*Sace upajjhāyassa cīvaraṃ kātabbaṃ hoti, saddhivihārikena kātabbaṃ, ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—**If the preceptor needs a robe, the student should make one himself,*";
P_HTM[11409]="*kinti nu kho upajjhāyassa cīvaraṃ kariyethāti.**or he should make an effort to get one made.*";
P_HTM[11410]="*Sace upajjhāyassa rajanā pacitabbā hoti, saddhivihārikena pacitabbā, ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—**If the preceptor needs dye, the student should make it himself,*";
P_HTM[11411]="*kinti nu kho upajjhāyassa rajanaṃ paciyethāti.**or he should make an effort to get it made.*";
P_HTM[11412]="*Sace upajjhāyassa cīvaraṃ rajitabbaṃ hoti, saddhivihārikena rajitabbaṃ, ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—**If the preceptor’s robe needs dyeing, the student should do it himself,*";
P_HTM[11413]="*kinti nu kho upajjhāyassa cīvaraṃ rajiyethāti.**or he should make an effort to get it done.*";
P_HTM[11414]="*Cīvaraṃ rajantena sādhukaṃ samparivattakaṃ samparivattakaṃ rajitabbaṃ, na ca acchinne theve pakkamitabbaṃ.**When he’s dyeing the robe, he should carefully and repeatedly turn it over, and he shouldn’t go away while it’s still dripping.*";
P_HTM[11415]="*Na upajjhāyaṃ anāpucchā ekaccassa patto dātabbo, na ekaccassa patto paṭiggahetabbo;**Without asking his preceptor for permission, he should not do any of the following: give away or receive a bowl;*";
P_HTM[11416]="*na ekaccassa cīvaraṃ dātabbaṃ, na ekaccassa cīvaraṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ;**give away or receive a robe;*";
P_HTM[11417]="*na ekaccassa parikkhāro dātabbo, na ekaccassa parikkhāro paṭiggahetabbo;**give away or receive a requisite;*";
P_HTM[11418]="*na ekaccassa kesā chedetabbā, na ekaccena kesā chedāpetabbā;**cut anyone’s hair or get it cut;*";
P_HTM[11419]="*na ekaccassa parikammaṃ kātabbaṃ, na ekaccena parikammaṃ kārāpetabbaṃ;**do work for anyone or get work done by anyone;*";
P_HTM[11420]="*na ekaccassa veyyāvacco kātabbo, na ekaccena veyyāvacco kārāpetabbo;**do a service for anyone or get a service done by anyone;*";
P_HTM[11421]="*na ekaccassa pacchāsamaṇena hotabbaṃ, na ekacco pacchāsamaṇo ādātabbo;**be the attendant monk for anyone or take anyone as his attendant monk;*";
P_HTM[11422]="*na ekaccassa piṇḍapāto nīharitabbo, na ekaccena piṇḍapāto nīharāpetabbo;**bring back almsfood for anyone or get almsfood brought back by anyone;*";
P_HTM[11423]="*na upajjhāyaṃ anāpucchā gāmo pavisitabbo;**enter the village,*";
P_HTM[11424]="*na susānaṃ gantabbaṃ;**go to the charnel ground,*";
P_HTM[11425]="*na disā pakkamitabbā.**or leave for another region.*";
P_HTM[11426]="*Sace upajjhāyo gilāno hoti, yāvajīvaṃ upaṭṭhātabbo, vuṭṭhānamassa āgametabbaṃ.**If his preceptor is sick, he should nurse him for as long as he lives, or he should wait until he has recovered.*";
P_HTM[11427]="*Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, saddhivihārikānaṃ upajjhāyesu vattaṃ yathā saddhivihārikehi upajjhāyesu sammā vattitabban”ti.**This is the proper conduct of a student toward his preceptor.”*";
P_HTM[11428]="*12. Saddhivihārikavattakathā**12. Discussion of the proper conduct toward a student*";
P_HTM[11429]="*Tena kho pana samayena upajjhāyā saddhivihārikesu na sammā vattanti.**At that time the preceptors were not conducting themselves properly toward their students.*";
P_HTM[11430]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11431]="*“kathañhi nāma upajjhāyā saddhivihārikesu na sammā vattissantī”ti.**“How can the preceptors not conduct themselves properly toward their students?”*";
P_HTM[11432]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[11433]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, upajjhāyā saddhivihārikesu na sammā vattantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the preceptors are not conducting themselves properly toward their students?”*";
P_HTM[11434]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[11435]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[11436]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[11437]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, upajjhāyānaṃ saddhivihārikesu vattaṃ paññapessāmi yathā upajjhāyehi saddhivihārikesu sammā vattitabbaṃ.**“Well then, I will lay down the proper conduct for preceptors toward their students.*";
P_HTM[11438]="*Upajjhāyena, bhikkhave, saddhivihārikamhi sammā vattitabbaṃ.**A preceptor should conduct himself properly toward his student.*";
P_HTM[11439]="*Tatrāyaṃ sammāvattanā—**This is the proper conduct:*";
P_HTM[11440]="*Upajjhāyena, bhikkhave, saddhivihāriko saṅgahetabbo anuggahetabbo uddesena paripucchāya ovādena anusāsaniyā.**A preceptor should help and take care of his student through recitation, questioning, and instruction.*";
P_HTM[11441]="*Sace upajjhāyassa patto hoti, saddhivihārikassa patto na hoti, upajjhāyena saddhivihārikassa patto dātabbo, ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—**If the preceptor has a bowl, but not the student, the preceptor should give it to him,*";
P_HTM[11442]="*kinti nu kho saddhivihārikassa patto uppajjiyethāti.**or he should make an effort to get him one.*";
P_HTM[11443]="*Sace upajjhāyassa cīvaraṃ hoti, saddhivihārikassa cīvaraṃ na hoti, upajjhāyena saddhivihārikassa cīvaraṃ dātabbaṃ, ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—**If the preceptor has a robe, but not the student, the preceptor should give it to him,*";
P_HTM[11444]="*kinti nu kho saddhivihārikassa cīvaraṃ uppajjiyethāti.**or he should make an effort to get him one.*";
P_HTM[11445]="*Sace upajjhāyassa parikkhāro hoti, saddhivihārikassa parikkhāro na hoti, upajjhāyena saddhivihārikassa parikkhāro dātabbo, ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—**If the preceptor has a requisite, but not the student, the preceptor should give it to him,*";
P_HTM[11446]="*kinti nu kho saddhivihārikassa parikkhāro uppajjiyethāti.**or he should make an effort to get him one.*";
P_HTM[11447]="*Sace saddhivihāriko gilāno hoti, kālasseva uṭṭhāya dantakaṭṭhaṃ dātabbaṃ, mukhodakaṃ dātabbaṃ, āsanaṃ paññapetabbaṃ.**If the student is sick, the preceptor should get up at the appropriate time and give his student a tooth cleaner and water for rinsing the mouth, and he should prepare a seat for him.*";
P_HTM[11448]="*Sace yāgu hoti, bhājanaṃ dhovitvā yāgu upanāmetabbā.**If there is rice porridge, he should wash a vessel and bring the rice porridge to his student.*";
P_HTM[11449]="*Yāguṃ pītassa udakaṃ datvā bhājanaṃ paṭiggahetvā nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena dhovitvā paṭisāmetabbaṃ.**When the student has drunk the rice porridge, the preceptor should give him water and receive the vessel. Holding it low, he should wash it carefully without scratching it and then put it away.*";
P_HTM[11450]="*Saddhivihārikamhi vuṭṭhite āsanaṃ uddharitabbaṃ.**When the student has gotten up, the preceptor should put away the seat.*";
P_HTM[11451]="*Sace so deso uklāpo hoti, so deso sammajjitabbo.**If the place is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11452]="*Sace saddhivihāriko gāmaṃ pavisitukāmo hoti, nivāsanaṃ dātabbaṃ, paṭinivāsanaṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ, kāyabandhanaṃ dātabbaṃ, saguṇaṃ katvā saṅghāṭiyo dātabbā, dhovitvā patto sodako dātabbo.**If the student wants to enter the village, the preceptor should give him a sarong and receive the one he’s wearing in return. He should give him a belt. He should put the other upper together, overlapping each other edge-to-edge, and then give them to him. He should wash his student’s bowl and give it to him while wet.*";
P_HTM[11453]="*Ettāvatā nivattissatīti āsanaṃ paññapetabbaṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ pādakathalikaṃ upanikkhipitabbaṃ, paccuggantvā pattacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ, paṭinivāsanaṃ dātabbaṃ, nivāsanaṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ.**Before he’s due back, the preceptor should prepare a seat and set out a foot stool, a foot scraper, and water for washing the feet. He should go out to meet the student and receive his bowl and robe. He should give him a sarong and receive the one he’s wearing in return.*";
P_HTM[11454]="*Sace cīvaraṃ sinnaṃ hoti, muhuttaṃ uṇhe otāpetabbaṃ, na ca uṇhe cīvaraṃ nidahitabbaṃ.**If the robe is moist, he should sun it for a short while, but he shouldn’t leave it in the heat.*";
P_HTM[11455]="*Cīvaraṃ saṅgharitabbaṃ.**He should fold the robe,*";
P_HTM[11456]="*Cīvaraṃ saṅgharantena caturaṅgulaṃ kaṇṇaṃ ussāretvā cīvaraṃ saṅgharitabbaṃ—**offsetting the edges by seven centimeters,*";
P_HTM[11457]="*mā majjhe bhaṅgo ahosīti.**so that the fold doesn’t become worn.*";
P_HTM[11458]="*Obhoge kāyabandhanaṃ kātabbaṃ.**He should place the belt in the fold.*";
P_HTM[11459]="*Sace piṇḍapāto hoti, saddhivihāriko ca bhuñjitukāmo hoti, udakaṃ datvā piṇḍapāto upanāmetabbo.**If there is almsfood and his student wants to eat, the preceptor should give him water and then the almsfood.*";
P_HTM[11460]="*Saddhivihāriko pānīyena pucchitabbo.**He should ask his student if he wants water to drink.*";
P_HTM[11461]="*Bhuttāvissa udakaṃ datvā pattaṃ paṭiggahetvā nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena dhovitvā vodakaṃ katvā muhuttaṃ uṇhe otāpetabbo, na ca uṇhe patto nidahitabbo.**When the student has eaten, the preceptor should give him water and receive his bowl. Holding it low, he should wash it carefully without scratching it. He should then dry it and sun it for a short while, but he shouldn’t leave it in the heat.*";
P_HTM[11462]="*Pattacīvaraṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ.**The preceptor should put away the robe and bowl.*";
P_HTM[11463]="*Pattaṃ nikkhipantena ekena hatthena pattaṃ gahetvā ekena hatthena heṭṭhāmañcaṃ vā heṭṭhāpīṭhaṃ vā parāmasitvā patto nikkhipitabbo.**When putting away the bowl, he should hold the bowl in one hand, feel under the bed or the bench with the other, and then put it away.*";
P_HTM[11464]="*Na ca anantarahitāya bhūmiyā patto nikkhipitabbo.**He shouldn’t put the bowl away on the bare floor.*";
P_HTM[11465]="*Cīvaraṃ nikkhipantena ekena hatthena cīvaraṃ gahetvā ekena hatthena cīvaravaṃsaṃ vā cīvararajjuṃ vā pamajjitvā pārato antaṃ orato bhogaṃ katvā cīvaraṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ.**When putting away the robe, he should hold the robe in one hand, wipe the bamboo robe rack or the clothesline with the other, and then put it away by folding the robe over it, making the ends face the wall and the fold face out.*";
P_HTM[11466]="*Saddhivihārikamhi vuṭṭhite āsanaṃ uddharitabbaṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ pādakathalikaṃ paṭisāmetabbaṃ.**When the student has gotten up, the preceptor should put away the seat and also the foot stool, the foot scraper, and the water for washing the feet.*";
P_HTM[11467]="*Sace so deso uklāpo hoti, so deso sammajjitabbo.**If the place is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11468]="*Sace saddhivihāriko nahāyitukāmo hoti, nahānaṃ paṭiyādetabbaṃ.**“If the student wants to bathe, the preceptor should prepare a bath.*";
P_HTM[11469]="*Sace sītena attho hoti, sītaṃ paṭiyādetabbaṃ.**If he wants a cold bath, he should prepare that;*";
P_HTM[11470]="*Sace uṇhena attho hoti, uṇhaṃ paṭiyādetabbaṃ.**if he wants a hot bath, he should prepare that.*";
P_HTM[11471]="*Sace saddhivihāriko jantāgharaṃ pavisitukāmo hoti, cuṇṇaṃ sannetabbaṃ, mattikā temetabbā, jantāgharapīṭhaṃ ādāya gantvā jantāgharapīṭhaṃ datvā cīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ, cuṇṇaṃ dātabbaṃ, mattikā dātabbā.**If the student wants to take a sauna, the preceptor should knead bath powder, moisten the clay, take a sauna stool, and go to the sauna. After giving his student the sauna stool, receiving his robe, and putting it aside, he should give him the bath powder and the clay.*";
P_HTM[11472]="*Sace ussahati jantāgharaṃ pavisitabbaṃ.**If he’s able, he should enter the sauna.*";
P_HTM[11473]="*Jantāgharaṃ pavisantena mattikāya mukhaṃ makkhetvā purato ca pacchato ca paṭicchādetvā jantāgharaṃ pavisitabbaṃ.**When entering the sauna, he should smear his face with clay, cover himself front and back, and then enter.*";
P_HTM[11474]="*Na there bhikkhū anupakhajja nisīditabbaṃ, na navā bhikkhū āsanena paṭibāhitabbā.**He shouldn’t sit encroaching on the senior monks, and he shouldn’t block the junior monks from getting a seat.*";
P_HTM[11475]="*Jantāghare saddhivihārikassa parikammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**While in the sauna, he should do services for his student.*";
P_HTM[11476]="*Jantāgharā nikkhamantena jantāgharapīṭhaṃ ādāya purato ca pacchato ca paṭicchādetvā jantāgharā nikkhamitabbaṃ.**When leaving the sauna, he should take the sauna stool, cover himself front and back, and then leave.*";
P_HTM[11477]="*Udakepi saddhivihārikassa parikammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**The preceptor should also do services for his student in the water.*";
P_HTM[11478]="*Nahātena paṭhamataraṃ uttaritvā attano gattaṃ vodakaṃ katvā nivāsetvā saddhivihārikassa gattato udakaṃ pamajjitabbaṃ, nivāsanaṃ dātabbaṃ, saṅghāṭi dātabbā, jantāgharapīṭhaṃ ādāya paṭhamataraṃ āgantvā āsanaṃ paññapetabbaṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ pādakathalikaṃ upanikkhipitabbaṃ.**When the preceptor has bathed, he should be the first to come out. He should dry himself and put on his sarong. He should then wipe the water off his student’s body, and he should give him his sarong and then his upper robe. Taking the sauna stool, he should be the first to return. He should prepare a seat, and also set out a foot stool, a foot scraper, and water for washing the feet.*";
P_HTM[11479]="*Saddhivihāriko pānīyena pucchitabbo.**He should ask his student if he wants water to drink.*";
P_HTM[11480]="*Yasmiṃ vihāre saddhivihāriko viharati, sace so vihāro uklāpo hoti, sace ussahati, sodhetabbo.**“If the dwelling where the student is staying is dirty, the preceptor should clean it if he’s able.*";
P_HTM[11481]="*Vihāraṃ sodhentena paṭhamaṃ pattacīvaraṃ nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ …pe…**When he’s cleaning the dwelling, he should first take out the bowl and robe and put them aside. He should take out the sitting mat and the sheet and put them aside. He should take out the mattress and the pillow and put them aside. Holding the bed low, he should carefully take it out without scratching it or knocking it against the door or the door frame, and he should put it aside. Holding the bench low, he should carefully take it out without scratching it or knocking it against the door or the door frame, and he should put it aside. He should take out the bed supports and put them aside. He should take out the spittoon and put it aside. He should take out the leaning board and put it aside. After taking note of its position, he should take out the floor cover and put it aside. If the dwelling has cobwebs, he should first remove them from the ceiling cloth, and he should then sweep the windows and the corners of the room. If the walls have been treated with red ocher and they’re moldy, he should moisten a cloth, wring it out, and wipe the walls. If the floor has been treated with a black finish and it’s moldy, he should moisten a cloth, wring it out, and wipe the floor. If the floor is untreated, he should sprinkle it with water and then sweep it, while trying to avoid stirring up dust. He should look out for any trash and discard it.*";
P_HTM[11482]="*sace ācamanakumbhiyā udakaṃ na hoti, ācamanakumbhiyā udakaṃ āsiñcitabbaṃ.**If there is no water in the rinsing pot, he should fill it.*";
P_HTM[11483]="*Sace saddhivihārikassa anabhirati uppannā hoti, upajjhāyena vūpakāsetabbo, vūpakāsāpetabbo, dhammakathā vāssa kātabbā.**“If the student becomes discontent with the spiritual life, the preceptor should send him away or have him sent away, or he should give him a teaching.*";
P_HTM[11484]="*Sace saddhivihārikassa kukkuccaṃ uppannaṃ hoti, upajjhāyena vinodetabbaṃ, vinodāpetabbaṃ, dhammakathā vāssa kātabbā.**If the student becomes anxious, the preceptor should dispel it or have it dispelled, or he should give him a teaching.*";
P_HTM[11485]="*Sace saddhivihārikassa diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ hoti, upajjhāyena vivecetabbaṃ, vivecāpetabbaṃ, dhammakathā vāssa kātabbā.**If the student has a wrong view, the preceptor should make him give it up or have someone else do it, or he should give him a teaching.*";
P_HTM[11486]="*Sace saddhivihāriko garudhammaṃ ajjhāpanno hoti parivāsāraho, upajjhāyena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**If the student has committed a heavy offense and deserves probation,*";
P_HTM[11487]="*kinti nu kho saṅgho saddhivihārikassa parivāsaṃ dadeyyāti.**the preceptor should try to get the Sangha to give it to him.*";
P_HTM[11488]="*Sace saddhivihāriko mūlāyapaṭikassanāraho hoti, upajjhāyena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**If the student has committed a heavy offense and deserves to be sent back to the beginning,*";
P_HTM[11489]="*kinti nu kho saṅgho saddhivihārikaṃ mūlāya paṭikasseyyāti.**the preceptor should try to get the Sangha to do it.*";
P_HTM[11490]="*Sace saddhivihāriko mānattāraho hoti, upajjhāyena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**If the student has committed a heavy offense and deserves the trial period,*";
P_HTM[11491]="*kinti nu kho saṅgho saddhivihārikassa mānattaṃ dadeyyāti.**the preceptor should try to get the Sangha to give it to him.*";
P_HTM[11492]="*Sace saddhivihāriko abbhānāraho hoti, upajjhāyena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**If the student has committed a heavy offense and deserves rehabilitation,*";
P_HTM[11493]="*kinti nu kho saṅgho saddhivihārikaṃ abbheyyāti.**the preceptor should try to get the Sangha to give it to him.*";
P_HTM[11494]="*Sace saṅgho saddhivihārikassa kammaṃ kattukāmo hoti, tajjanīyaṃ vā niyassaṃ vā pabbājanīyaṃ vā paṭisāraṇīyaṃ vā ukkhepanīyaṃ vā, upajjhāyena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**If the Sangha wants to do a legal procedure against his student—whether a procedure of condemnation, demotion, banishment, reconciliation, or ejection—*";
P_HTM[11495]="*kinti nu kho saṅgho saddhivihārikassa kammaṃ na kareyya, lahukāya vā pariṇāmeyyāti.**the preceptor should make an effort to stop it or to reduce the penalty.*";
P_HTM[11496]="*Kataṃ vā panassa hoti saṅghena kammaṃ, tajjanīyaṃ vā niyassaṃ vā pabbājanīyaṃ vā paṭisāraṇīyaṃ vā, ukkhepanīyaṃ vā, upajjhāyena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**But if the Sangha has already done a legal procedure against his student—whether a procedure of condemnation, demotion, banishment, reconciliation, or ejection—*";
P_HTM[11497]="*kinti nu kho saddhivihāriko sammā vatteyya lomaṃ pāteyya, netthāraṃ vatteyya, saṅgho taṃ kammaṃ paṭippassambheyyāti.**the preceptor should help the student conduct himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and try to get the Sangha to lift that procedure.*";
P_HTM[11498]="*Sace saddhivihārikassa cīvaraṃ dhovitabbaṃ hoti, upajjhāyena ācikkhitabbaṃ—evaṃ dhoveyyāsīti,**“If the student’s robe needs washing, the preceptor should show him how to do it,*";
P_HTM[11499]="*ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—kinti nu kho saddhivihārikassa cīvaraṃ dhoviyethāti.**or he should make an effort to get it done.*";
P_HTM[11500]="*Sace saddhivihārikassa cīvaraṃ kātabbaṃ hoti, upajjhāyena ācikkhitabbaṃ—evaṃ kareyyāsīti,**If the student needs a robe, the preceptor should show him how to make one,*";
P_HTM[11501]="*ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—kinti nu kho saddhivihārikassa cīvaraṃ kariyethāti.**or he should make an effort to get one made.*";
P_HTM[11502]="*Sace saddhivihārikassa rajanaṃ pacitabbaṃ hoti, upajjhāyena ācikkhitabbaṃ—evaṃ paceyyāsīti,**If the student needs dye, the preceptor should show him how to make it,*";
P_HTM[11503]="*ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—kinti nu kho saddhivihārikassa rajanaṃ paciyethāti.**or he should make an effort to get it made.*";
P_HTM[11504]="*Sace saddhivihārikassa cīvaraṃ rajitabbaṃ hoti, upajjhāyena ācikkhitabbaṃ—evaṃ rajeyyāsīti,**If the student’s robe needs dyeing, the preceptor should show him how to do it,*";
P_HTM[11505]="*ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—kinti nu kho saddhivihārikassa cīvaraṃ rajiyethāti.**or he should make an effort to get it done.*";
P_HTM[11506]="*Cīvaraṃ rajantena sādhukaṃ samparivattakaṃ samparivattakaṃ rajitabbaṃ, na ca acchinne theve pakkamitabbaṃ.**When he’s dyeing the robe, he should carefully and repeatedly turn it over, and he shouldn’t go away while it’s still dripping.*";
P_HTM[11507]="*Sace saddhivihāriko gilāno hoti, yāvajīvaṃ upaṭṭhātabbo, vuṭṭhānamassa āgametabbaṃ.**If his student is sick, he should nurse him for as long as he lives, or he should wait until he has recovered.*";
P_HTM[11508]="*Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, upajjhāyānaṃ saddhivihārikesu vattaṃ yathā upajjhāyehi saddhivihārikesu sammā vattitabban”ti.**This is the proper conduct of a preceptor toward his student.”*";
P_HTM[11509]="*Dutiyabhāṇavāro niṭṭhito.**The second section for recitation is finished.*";
P_HTM[11510]="*13. Ācariyavattakathā**13. Discussion of the proper conduct toward a teacher*";
P_HTM[11511]="*Tena kho pana samayena antevāsikā ācariyesu na sammā vattanti.**At that time the pupils were not conducting themselves properly toward their teachers.*";
P_HTM[11512]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11513]="*“kathañhi nāma antevāsikā ācariyesu na sammā vattissantī”ti.**“How can the pupils not conduct themselves properly toward their teachers?”*";
P_HTM[11514]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[11515]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, antevāsikā ācariyesu na sammā vattantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the pupils are not conducting themselves properly toward their teachers?”*";
P_HTM[11516]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[11517]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[11518]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[11519]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, antevāsikānaṃ ācariyesu vattaṃ paññapessāmi yathā antevāsikehi ācariyesu sammā vattitabbaṃ.**“Well then, I will lay down the proper conduct for a pupil toward his teacher.*";
P_HTM[11520]="*Antevāsikena, bhikkhave, ācariyamhi sammā vattitabbaṃ.**A pupil should conduct himself properly toward his teacher.*";
P_HTM[11521]="*Tatrāyaṃ sammāvattanā—**This is the proper conduct:*";
P_HTM[11522]="*Kālasseva uṭṭhāya upāhanā omuñcitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā dantakaṭṭhaṃ dātabbaṃ, mukhodakaṃ dātabbaṃ, āsanaṃ paññapetabbaṃ.**Having gotten up at the appropriate time, the pupil should take off his sandals, and put his upper robe over one shoulder. He should then give his teacher a tooth cleaner and water for rinsing the mouth, and he should prepare a seat for him.*";
P_HTM[11523]="*Sace yāgu hoti, bhājanaṃ dhovitvā yāgu upanāmetabbā.**If there is rice porridge, he should wash a vessel and bring the rice porridge to his teacher.*";
P_HTM[11524]="*Yāguṃ pītassa udakaṃ datvā bhājanaṃ paṭiggahetvā nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena dhovitvā paṭisāmetabbaṃ.**When the teacher has drunk the rice porridge, the pupil should give him water and receive the vessel. Holding it low, he should wash it carefully without scratching it and then put it away.*";
P_HTM[11525]="*Ācariyamhi vuṭṭhite āsanaṃ uddharitabbaṃ.**When the teacher has gotten up, the pupil should put away the seat.*";
P_HTM[11526]="*Sace so deso uklāpo hoti, so deso sammajjitabbo.**If the place is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11527]="*Sace ācariyo gāmaṃ pavisitukāmo hoti, nivāsanaṃ dātabbaṃ, paṭinivāsanaṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ, kāyabandhanaṃ dātabbaṃ, saguṇaṃ katvā saṅghāṭiyo dātabbā, dhovitvā patto sodako dātabbo.**If the teacher wants to enter the village, the pupil should give him a sarong and receive the one he’s wearing in return. He should give him a belt. He should put the upper robes together, overlapping each other edge-to-edge, and then give them to him. He should wash his teacher’s bowl and give it to him while wet.*";
P_HTM[11528]="*Sace ācariyo pacchāsamaṇaṃ ākaṅkhati, timaṇḍalaṃ paṭicchādentena parimaṇḍalaṃ nivāsetvā kāyabandhanaṃ bandhitvā saguṇaṃ katvā saṅghāṭiyo pārupitvā gaṇṭhikaṃ paṭimuñcitvā dhovitvā pattaṃ gahetvā ācariyassa pacchāsamaṇena hotabbaṃ.**If the teacher wants an attendant, the pupil should put on his sarong evenly all around, covering the navel and the knees. He should put on a belt. Putting the upper robes together, overlapping each other edge-to-edge, he should put them on and fasten the toggle. He should wash his bowl, bring it along, and be his teacher’s attendant.*";
P_HTM[11529]="*Nātidūre gantabbaṃ, nāccāsanne gantabbaṃ, pattapariyāpannaṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ.**He shouldn’t walk too far behind his teacher or too close to him. He should receive the contents of his bowl.*";
P_HTM[11530]="*Na ācariyassa bhaṇamānassa antarantarā kathā opātetabbā.**He shouldn’t interrupt his teacher when he’s speaking.*";
P_HTM[11531]="*Ācariyo āpattisāmantā bhaṇamāno nivāretabbo.**But if the teacher’s speech is bordering on an offense, he should stop him.*";
P_HTM[11532]="*Nivattantena paṭhamataraṃ āgantvā āsanaṃ paññapetabbaṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ pādakathalikaṃ upanikkhipitabbaṃ, paccuggantvā pattacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ, paṭinivāsanaṃ dātabbaṃ, nivāsanaṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ.**When returning, the pupil should go first to prepare a seat and to set out a foot stool, a foot scraper, and water for washing the feet. He should go out to meet the teacher and receive his bowl and robe. He should give him a sarong and receive the one he’s wearing in return.*";
P_HTM[11533]="*Sace cīvaraṃ sinnaṃ hoti, muhuttaṃ uṇhe otāpetabbaṃ, na ca uṇhe cīvaraṃ nidahitabbaṃ.**If the robe is moist, he should sun it for a short while, but he shouldn’t leave it in the heat.*";
P_HTM[11534]="*Cīvaraṃ saṅgharitabbaṃ.**He should fold the robe,*";
P_HTM[11535]="*Cīvaraṃ saṅgharantena caturaṅgulaṃ kaṇṇaṃ ussāretvā cīvaraṃ saṅgharitabbaṃ—**offsetting the edges by seven centimeters,*";
P_HTM[11536]="*mā majjhe bhaṅgo ahosīti.**so that the fold doesn’t become worn.*";
P_HTM[11537]="*Obhoge kāyabandhanaṃ kātabbaṃ.**He should place the belt in the fold.*";
P_HTM[11538]="*Sace piṇḍapāto hoti, ācariyo ca bhuñjitukāmo hoti, udakaṃ datvā piṇḍapāto upanāmetabbo.**If there is almsfood and his teacher wants to eat, the pupil should give him water and then the almsfood.*";
P_HTM[11539]="*Ācariyo pānīyena pucchitabbo.**He should ask his teacher if he wants water to drink.*";
P_HTM[11540]="*Bhuttāvissa udakaṃ datvā pattaṃ paṭiggahetvā nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena dhovitvā vodakaṃ katvā muhuttaṃ uṇhe otāpetabbo, na ca uṇhe patto nidahitabbo.**When the teacher has eaten, the pupil should give him water and receive his bowl. Holding it low, he should wash it carefully without scratching it. He should then dry it and sun it for a short while, but he shouldn’t leave it in the heat.*";
P_HTM[11541]="*Pattacīvaraṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ.**The pupil should put away the robe and bowl.*";
P_HTM[11542]="*Pattaṃ nikkhipantena ekena hatthena pattaṃ gahetvā ekena hatthena heṭṭhāmañcaṃ vā heṭṭhāpīṭhaṃ vā parāmasitvā patto nikkhipitabbo.**When putting away the bowl, he should hold the bowl in one hand, feel under the bed or the bench with the other, and then put it away.*";
P_HTM[11543]="*Na ca anantarahitāya bhūmiyā patto nikkhipitabbo.**He shouldn’t put the bowl away on the bare floor.*";
P_HTM[11544]="*Cīvaraṃ nikkhipantena ekena hatthena cīvaraṃ gahetvā ekena hatthena cīvaravaṃsaṃ vā cīvararajjuṃ vā pamajjitvā pārato antaṃ orato bhogaṃ katvā cīvaraṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ.**When putting away the robe, he should hold the robe in one hand, wipe the bamboo robe rack or the clothesline with the other, and then put it away by folding the robe over it, making the ends face the wall and the fold face out.*";
P_HTM[11545]="*Ācariyamhi vuṭṭhite āsanaṃ uddharitabbaṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ pādakathalikaṃ paṭisāmetabbaṃ.**When the teacher has gotten up, the pupil should put away the seat and also the foot stool, the foot scraper, and the water for washing the feet.*";
P_HTM[11546]="*Sace so deso uklāpo hoti, so deso sammajjitabbo.**If the place is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11547]="*Sace ācariyo nahāyitukāmo hoti, nahānaṃ paṭiyādetabbaṃ.**“If the teacher wants to bathe, the pupil should prepare a bath.*";
P_HTM[11548]="*Sace sītena attho hoti, sītaṃ paṭiyādetabbaṃ.**If he wants a cold bath, he should prepare that;*";
P_HTM[11549]="*Sace uṇhena attho hoti, uṇhaṃ paṭiyādetabbaṃ.**if he wants a hot bath, he should prepare that.*";
P_HTM[11550]="*Sace ācariyo jantāgharaṃ pavisitukāmo hoti, cuṇṇaṃ sannetabbaṃ, mattikā temetabbā, jantāgharapīṭhaṃ ādāya ācariyassa piṭṭhito piṭṭhito gantvā jantāgharapīṭhaṃ datvā cīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ, cuṇṇaṃ dātabbaṃ, mattikā dātabbā.**If the teacher wants to take a sauna, the pupil should knead bath powder, moisten the clay, take a sauna stool, and follow behind his teacher. After giving the teacher the sauna stool, receiving his robe, and putting it aside, he should give him the bath powder and the clay.*";
P_HTM[11551]="*Sace ussahati, jantāgharaṃ pavisitabbaṃ.**If he’s able, he should enter the sauna.*";
P_HTM[11552]="*Jantāgharaṃ pavisantena mattikāya mukhaṃ makkhetvā purato ca pacchato ca paṭicchādetvā jantāgharaṃ pavisitabbaṃ.**When entering the sauna, he should smear his face with clay, cover himself front and back, and then enter.*";
P_HTM[11553]="*Na there bhikkhū anupakhajja nisīditabbaṃ.**He shouldn’t sit encroaching on the senior monks,*";
P_HTM[11554]="*Na navā bhikkhū āsanena paṭibāhitabbā.**and he shouldn’t block the junior monks from getting a seat.*";
P_HTM[11555]="*Jantāghare ācariyassa parikammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**While in the sauna, he should do services for his teacher.*";
P_HTM[11556]="*Jantāgharā nikkhamantena jantāgharapīṭhaṃ ādāya purato ca pacchato ca paṭicchādetvā jantāgharā nikkhamitabbaṃ.**When leaving the sauna, he should take the sauna stool, cover himself front and back, and then leave.*";
P_HTM[11557]="*Udakepi ācariyassa parikammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**He should also do services for his teacher in the water.*";
P_HTM[11558]="*Nahātena paṭhamataraṃ uttaritvā attano gattaṃ vodakaṃ katvā nivāsetvā ācariyassa gattato udakaṃ pamajjitabbaṃ, nivāsanaṃ dātabbaṃ, saṅghāṭi dātabbā, jantāgharapīṭhaṃ ādāya paṭhamataraṃ āgantvā āsanaṃ paññapetabbaṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ pādakathalikaṃ upanikkhipitabbaṃ.**When he has bathed, he should be the first to come out. He should dry himself and put on his sarong. He should then wipe the water off his teacher’s body, and he should give him his sarong and then his upper robe. Taking the sauna stool, he should be the first to return. He should prepare a seat, and also set out a foot stool, a foot scraper, and water for washing the feet.*";
P_HTM[11559]="*Ācariyo pānīyena pucchitabbo.**He should ask his teacher if he wants water to drink.*";
P_HTM[11560]="*Sace uddisāpetukāmo hoti, uddisitabbo.**If the teacher wants him to recite, he should do so.*";
P_HTM[11561]="*Sace paripucchitukāmo hoti, paripucchitabbo.**If the teacher wants to question him, he should be questioned.*";
P_HTM[11562]="*Yasmiṃ vihāre ācariyo viharati, sace so vihāro uklāpo hoti, sace ussahati, sodhetabbo.**“If the dwelling where the teacher is staying is dirty, the pupil should clean it if he’s able.*";
P_HTM[11563]="*Vihāraṃ sodhentena paṭhamaṃ pattacīvaraṃ nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ;**When he’s cleaning the dwelling, he should first take out the bowl and robe and put them aside.*";
P_HTM[11564]="*nisīdanapaccattharaṇaṃ nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ;**He should take out the sitting mat and the sheet and put them aside.*";
P_HTM[11565]="*bhisibibbohanaṃ nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ;**He should take out the mattress and the pillow and put them aside.*";
P_HTM[11566]="*mañco nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena asaṅghaṭṭentena kavāṭapiṭṭhaṃ, nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbo;**Holding the bed low, he should carefully take it out without scratching it or knocking it against the door or the door frame, and he should put it aside.*";
P_HTM[11567]="*pīṭhaṃ nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena, asaṅghaṭṭentena kavāṭapiṭṭhaṃ, nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ;**Holding the bench low, he should carefully take it out without scratching it or knocking it against the door or the door frame, and he should put it aside.*";
P_HTM[11568]="*mañcapaṭipādakā nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbā;**He should take out the bed supports and put them aside.*";
P_HTM[11569]="*kheḷamallako nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbo;**He should take out the spittoon and put it aside.*";
P_HTM[11570]="*apassenaphalakaṃ nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ;**He should take out the leaning board and put it aside.*";
P_HTM[11571]="*bhūmattharaṇaṃ yathāpaññattaṃ sallakkhetvā nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ.**After taking note of its position, he should take out the floor cover and put it aside.*";
P_HTM[11572]="*Sace vihāre santānakaṃ hoti, ullokā paṭhamaṃ ohāretabbaṃ, ālokasandhikaṇṇabhāgā pamajjitabbā.**If the dwelling has cobwebs, he should first remove them from the ceiling cloth, and he should then wipe the windows and the corners of the room.*";
P_HTM[11573]="*Sace gerukaparikammakatā bhitti kaṇṇakitā hoti, coḷakaṃ temetvā pīḷetvā pamajjitabbā.**If the walls have been treated with red ocher and they’re moldy, he should moisten a cloth, wring it out, and wipe the walls.*";
P_HTM[11574]="*Sace kāḷavaṇṇakatā bhūmi kaṇṇakitā hoti, coḷakaṃ temetvā pīḷetvā pamajjitabbā.**If the floor has been treated with a black finish and it’s moldy, he should moisten a cloth, wring it out, and wipe the floor.*";
P_HTM[11575]="*Sace akatā hoti bhūmi, udakena paripphositvā paripphositvā sammajjitabbā—**If the floor is untreated, he should sprinkle it with water and then sweep it,*";
P_HTM[11576]="*mā vihāro rajena uhaññīti.**while trying to avoid stirring up dust.*";
P_HTM[11577]="*Saṅkāraṃ vicinitvā ekamantaṃ chaḍḍetabbaṃ.**He should look out for any trash and discard it.*";
P_HTM[11578]="*Bhūmattharaṇaṃ otāpetvā sodhetvā papphoṭetvā atiharitvā yathāpaññattaṃ paññapetabbaṃ.**He should sun the floor cover, clean it, beat it, bring it back inside, and put it back as before.*";
P_HTM[11579]="*Mañcapaṭipādakā otāpetvā pamajjitvā atiharitvā yathāṭhāne ṭhapetabbā.**He should sun the bed supports, wipe them, bring them back inside, and put them back where they were.*";
P_HTM[11580]="*Mañco otāpetvā sodhetvā papphoṭetvā nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena, asaṅghaṭṭentena kavāṭapiṭṭhaṃ, atiharitvā yathāpaññattaṃ paññapetabbo.**He should sun the bed, clean it, and beat it. Holding it low, he should carefully bring it back inside without scratching it or knocking it against the door or the door frame, and he should put it back as before.*";
P_HTM[11581]="*Pīṭhaṃ otāpetvā sodhetvā papphoṭetvā nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena, asaṅghaṭṭentena kavāṭapiṭṭhaṃ, atiharitvā yathāpaññattaṃ paññapetabbaṃ.**He should sun the bench, clean it, and beat it. Holding it low, he should carefully bring it back inside without scratching it or knocking it against the door or the door frame, and he should put it back as before.*";
P_HTM[11582]="*Bhisibibbohanaṃ otāpetvā sodhetvā papphoṭetvā atiharitvā yathāpaññattaṃ paññapetabbaṃ.**He should sun the mattress and the pillow, clean them, beat them, bring them back inside, and put them back as before.*";
P_HTM[11583]="*Nisīdanapaccattharaṇaṃ otāpetvā sodhetvā papphoṭetvā atiharitvā yathāpaññattaṃ paññapetabbaṃ.**He should sun the sitting mat and the sheet, clean them, beat them, bring them back inside, and put them back as before.*";
P_HTM[11584]="*Kheḷamallako otāpetvā pamajjitvā atiharitvā yathāṭhāne ṭhapetabbo.**He should sun the spittoon, wipe it, bring it back inside, and put it back where it was.*";
P_HTM[11585]="*Apassenaphalakaṃ otāpetvā pamajjitvā atiharitvā yathāṭhāne ṭhapetabbaṃ.**He should sun the leaning board, wipe it, bring it back inside, and put it back where it was.*";
P_HTM[11586]="*Pattacīvaraṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ.**He should put away the bowl and robe.*";
P_HTM[11587]="*Pattaṃ nikkhipantena ekena hatthena pattaṃ gahetvā ekena hatthena heṭṭhāmañcaṃ vā heṭṭhāpīṭhaṃ vā parāmasitvā patto nikkhipitabbo.**When putting away the bowl, he should hold the bowl in one hand, feel under the bed or the bench with the other, and then put it away.*";
P_HTM[11588]="*Na ca anantarahitāya bhūmiyā patto nikkhipitabbo.**He shouldn’t put the bowl away on the bare floor.*";
P_HTM[11589]="*Cīvaraṃ nikkhipantena ekena hatthena cīvaraṃ gahetvā ekena hatthena cīvaravaṃsaṃ vā cīvararajjuṃ vā pamajjitvā pārato antaṃ orato bhogaṃ katvā cīvaraṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ.**When putting away the robe, he should hold the robe in one hand, wipe the bamboo robe rack or the clothesline with the other, and then put it away by folding the robe over it, making the ends face the wall and the fold face out.*";
P_HTM[11590]="*Sace puratthimā sarajā vātā vāyanti, puratthimā vātapānā thaketabbā.**If dusty winds are blowing from the east, he should close the windows on the eastern side.*";
P_HTM[11591]="*Sace pacchimā sarajā vātā vāyanti, pacchimā vātapānā thaketabbā.**If dusty winds are blowing from the west, he should close the windows on the western side.*";
P_HTM[11592]="*Sace uttarā sarajā vātā vāyanti, uttarā vātapānā thaketabbā.**If dusty winds are blowing from the north, he should close the windows on the northern side.*";
P_HTM[11593]="*Sace dakkhiṇā sarajā vātā vāyanti, dakkhiṇā vātapānā thaketabbā.**If dusty winds are blowing from the south, he should close the windows on the southern side.*";
P_HTM[11594]="*Sace sītakālo hoti, divā vātapānā vivaritabbā, rattiṃ thaketabbā.**If the weather is cold, he should open the windows during the day and close them at night.*";
P_HTM[11595]="*Sace uṇhakālo hoti, divā vātapānā thaketabbā, rattiṃ vivaritabbā.**If the weather is hot, he should close the windows during the day and open them at night.*";
P_HTM[11596]="*Sace pariveṇaṃ uklāpaṃ hoti, pariveṇaṃ sammajjitabbaṃ.**If the precincts are dirty, he should sweep them.*";
P_HTM[11597]="*Sace koṭṭhako uklāpo hoti, koṭṭhako sammajjitabbo.**If the gateway is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11598]="*Sace upaṭṭhānasālā uklāpā hoti, upaṭṭhānasālā sammajjitabbā.**If the assembly hall is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11599]="*Sace aggisālā uklāpā hoti, aggisālā sammajjitabbā.**If the water-boiling shed is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11600]="*Sace vaccakuṭi uklāpā hoti, vaccakuṭi sammajjitabbā.**If the restroom is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11601]="*Sace pānīyaṃ na hoti, pānīyaṃ upaṭṭhāpetabbaṃ.**If there is no water for drinking, he should get some.*";
P_HTM[11602]="*Sace paribhojanīyaṃ na hoti, paribhojanīyaṃ upaṭṭhāpetabbaṃ.**If there is no water for washing, he should get some.*";
P_HTM[11603]="*Sace ācamanakumbhiyā udakaṃ na hoti, ācamanakumbhiyā udakaṃ āsiñcitabbaṃ.**If there is no water in the rinsing pot, he should fill it.*";
P_HTM[11604]="*Sace ācariyassa anabhirati uppannā hoti, antevāsikena vūpakāsetabbo, vūpakāsāpetabbo, dhammakathā vāssa kātabbā.**“If the teacher becomes discontent with the spiritual life, the pupil should send him away or have him sent away, or he should give him a teaching.*";
P_HTM[11605]="*Sace ācariyassa kukkuccaṃ uppannaṃ hoti, antevāsikena vinodetabbaṃ, vinodāpetabbaṃ, dhammakathā vāssa kātabbā.**If the teacher becomes anxious, the pupil should dispel it or have it dispelled, or he should give him a teaching.*";
P_HTM[11606]="*Sace ācariyassa diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ hoti, antevāsikena vivecetabbaṃ, vivecāpetabbaṃ, dhammakathā vāssa kātabbā.**If the teacher has a wrong view, the pupil should make him give it up or have someone else do it, or he should give him a teaching.*";
P_HTM[11607]="*Sace ācariyo garudhammaṃ ajjhāpanno hoti, parivāsāraho, antevāsikena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**If the teacher has committed a heavy offense and deserves probation,*";
P_HTM[11608]="*kinti nu kho saṅgho ācariyassa parivāsaṃ dadeyyāti.**the pupil should try to get the Sangha to give it to him.*";
P_HTM[11609]="*Sace ācariyo mūlāyapaṭikassanāraho hoti, antevāsikena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**If the teacher has committed a heavy offense and deserves to be sent back to the beginning,*";
P_HTM[11610]="*kinti nu kho saṅgho ācariyaṃ mūlāya paṭikasseyyāti.**the pupil should try to get the Sangha to do it.*";
P_HTM[11611]="*Sace ācariyo mānattāraho hoti, antevāsikena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**If the teacher has committed a heavy offense and deserves the trial period,*";
P_HTM[11612]="*kinti nu kho saṅgho ācariyassa mānattaṃ dadeyyāti.**the pupil should try to get the Sangha to give it to him.*";
P_HTM[11613]="*Sace ācariyo abbhānāraho hoti, antevāsikena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**If the teacher has committed a heavy offense and deserves rehabilitation,*";
P_HTM[11614]="*kinti nu kho saṅgho ācariyaṃ abbheyyāti.**the pupil should try to get the Sangha to give it to him.*";
P_HTM[11615]="*Sace saṅgho ācariyassa kammaṃ kattukāmo hoti, tajjanīyaṃ vā niyassaṃ vā pabbājanīyaṃ vā paṭisāraṇīyaṃ vā ukkhepanīyaṃ vā, antevāsikena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**If the Sangha wants to do a legal procedure against his teacher—whether a procedure of condemnation, demotion, banishment, reconciliation, or ejection—*";
P_HTM[11616]="*kinti nu kho saṅgho ācariyassa kammaṃ na kareyya, lahukāya vā pariṇāmeyyāti.**the pupil should make an effort to stop it or to reduce the penalty.*";
P_HTM[11617]="*Kataṃ vā panassa hoti saṅghena kammaṃ, tajjanīyaṃ vā niyassaṃ vā pabbājanīyaṃ vā paṭisāraṇīyaṃ vā ukkhepanīyaṃ vā, antevāsikena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**But if the Sangha has already done a legal procedure against his teacher—whether a procedure of condemnation, demotion, banishment, reconciliation, or ejection—*";
P_HTM[11618]="*kinti nu kho ācariyo sammā vatteyya, lomaṃ pāteyya, netthāraṃ vatteyya, saṅgho taṃ kammaṃ paṭippassambheyyāti.**the pupil should help the teacher conduct himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and try to get the Sangha to lift that procedure.*";
P_HTM[11619]="*Sace ācariyassa cīvaraṃ dhovitabbaṃ hoti, antevāsikena dhovitabbaṃ, ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—**“If the teacher’s robe needs washing, the pupil should do it himself,*";
P_HTM[11620]="*kinti nu kho ācariyassa cīvaraṃ dhoviyethāti.**or he should make an effort to get it done.*";
P_HTM[11621]="*Sace ācariyassa cīvaraṃ kātabbaṃ hoti, antevāsikena kātabbaṃ, ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—**If the teacher needs a robe, the pupil should make one himself,*";
P_HTM[11622]="*kinti nu kho ācariyassa cīvaraṃ kariyethāti.**or he should make an effort to get one made.*";
P_HTM[11623]="*Sace ācariyassa rajanaṃ pacitabbaṃ hoti, antevāsikena pacitabbaṃ, ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—**If the teacher needs dye, the pupil should make it himself,*";
P_HTM[11624]="*kinti nu kho ācariyassa rajanaṃ paciyethāti.**or he should make an effort to get it made.*";
P_HTM[11625]="*Sace ācariyassa cīvaraṃ rajitabbaṃ hoti, antevāsikena rajitabbaṃ, ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—**If the teacher’s robe needs dyeing, the pupil should do it himself,*";
P_HTM[11626]="*kinti nu kho ācariyassa cīvaraṃ rajiyethāti.**or he should make an effort to get it done.*";
P_HTM[11627]="*Cīvaraṃ rajantena sādhukaṃ samparivattakaṃ samparivattakaṃ rajitabbaṃ, na ca acchinne theve pakkamitabbaṃ.**When he’s dyeing the robe, he should carefully and repeatedly turn it over, and he shouldn’t go away while it’s still dripping.*";
P_HTM[11628]="*Na ācariyaṃ anāpucchā ekaccassa patto dātabbo, na ekaccassa patto paṭiggahetabbo;**Without asking his teacher for permission, he shouldn’t do any of the following: give away or receive a bowl;*";
P_HTM[11629]="*na ekaccassa cīvaraṃ dātabbaṃ, na ekaccassa cīvaraṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ;**give away or receive a robe;*";
P_HTM[11630]="*na ekaccassa parikkhāro dātabbo, na ekaccassa parikkhāro paṭiggahetabbo;**give away or receive a requisite;*";
P_HTM[11631]="*na ekaccassa kesā cheditabbā, na ekaccena kesā chedāpetabbā;**cut anyone’s hair or get it cut;*";
P_HTM[11632]="*na ekaccassa parikammaṃ kātabbaṃ, na ekaccena parikammaṃ kārāpetabbaṃ;**do work for anyone or get work done by anyone;*";
P_HTM[11633]="*na ekaccassa veyyāvacco kātabbo, na ekaccena veyyāvacco kārāpetabbo;**do a service for anyone or get a service done by anyone;*";
P_HTM[11634]="*na ekaccassa pacchāsamaṇena hotabbaṃ, na ekacco pacchāsamaṇo ādātabbo;**be the attendant monk for anyone or take anyone as his attendant monk;*";
P_HTM[11635]="*na ekaccassa piṇḍapāto nīharitabbo, na ekaccena piṇḍapāto nīharāpetabbo;**bring back almsfood for anyone or get almsfood brought back by anyone;*";
P_HTM[11636]="*na ācariyaṃ anāpucchā gāmo pavisitabbo;**enter the village,*";
P_HTM[11637]="*na susānaṃ gantabbaṃ;**go to the charnel ground,*";
P_HTM[11638]="*na disā pakkamitabbā.**or leave for another region.*";
P_HTM[11639]="*Sace ācariyo gilāno hoti, yāvajīvaṃ upaṭṭhātabbo, vuṭṭhānamassa āgametabbaṃ.**If his teacher is sick, he should nurse him for as long as he lives, or he should wait until he has recovered.*";
P_HTM[11640]="*Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, antevāsikānaṃ ācariyesu vattaṃ yathā antevāsikehi ācariyesu sammā vattitabban”ti.**This is the proper conduct of a pupil toward his teacher.”*";
P_HTM[11641]="*14. Antevāsikavattakathā**14. Discussion of the proper conduct toward a pupil*";
P_HTM[11642]="*Tena kho pana samayena ācariyā antevāsikesu na sammā vattanti.**At that time the teachers were not conducting themselves properly toward their pupils.*";
P_HTM[11643]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11644]="*“kathañhi nāma ācariyā antevāsikesu na sammā vattissantī”ti.**“How can the teachers not conduct themselves properly toward their pupils?”*";
P_HTM[11645]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[11646]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[11647]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, ācariyā antevāsikesu na sammā vattantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the teachers are not conducting themselves properly toward their pupils?”*";
P_HTM[11648]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[11649]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[11650]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[11651]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, ācariyānaṃ antevāsikesu vattaṃ paññapessāmi yathā ācariyehi antevāsikesu sammā vattitabbaṃ.**“Well then, I will lay down the proper conduct for a teacher toward his pupil.*";
P_HTM[11652]="*Ācariyena, bhikkhave, antevāsikamhi sammā vattitabbaṃ.**A teacher should conduct himself properly toward his pupil.*";
P_HTM[11653]="*Tatrāyaṃ sammāvattanā—**This is the proper conduct:*";
P_HTM[11654]="*Ācariyena, bhikkhave, antevāsiko saṅgahetabbo anuggahetabbo uddesena paripucchāya ovādena anusāsaniyā.**A teacher should help and take care of his pupil through recitation, questioning, and instruction.*";
P_HTM[11655]="*Sace ācariyassa patto hoti, antevāsikassa patto na hoti, ācariyena antevāsikassa patto dātabbo, ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—**If the teacher has a bowl, but not the pupil, the teacher should give it to him,*";
P_HTM[11656]="*kinti nu kho antevāsikassa patto uppajjiyethāti.**or he should make an effort to get him one.*";
P_HTM[11657]="*Sace ācariyassa cīvaraṃ hoti, antevāsikassa cīvaraṃ na hoti, ācariyena antevāsikassa cīvaraṃ dātabbaṃ, ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—**If the teacher has a robe, but not the pupil, the teacher should give it to him,*";
P_HTM[11658]="*kinti nu kho antevāsikassa cīvaraṃ uppajjiyethāti.**or he should make an effort to get him one.*";
P_HTM[11659]="*Sace ācariyassa parikkhāro hoti, antevāsikassa parikkhāro na hoti, ācariyena antevāsikassa parikkhāro dātabbo, ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—**If the teacher has a requisite, but not the pupil, the teacher should give it to him,*";
P_HTM[11660]="*kinti nu kho antevāsikassa parikkhāro uppajjiyethāti.**or he should make an effort to get him one.*";
P_HTM[11661]="*Sace antevāsiko gilāno hoti, kālasseva uṭṭhāya dantakaṭṭhaṃ dātabbaṃ, mukhodakaṃ dātabbaṃ, āsanaṃ paññapetabbaṃ.**If the pupil is sick, the teacher should get up at the appropriate time and give his pupil a tooth cleaner and water for rinsing the mouth, and he should prepare a seat for him.*";
P_HTM[11662]="*Sace yāgu hoti, bhājanaṃ dhovitvā yāgu upanāmetabbā.**If there is rice porridge, he should wash a vessel and bring the rice porridge to his pupil.*";
P_HTM[11663]="*Yāguṃ pītassa udakaṃ datvā bhājanaṃ paṭiggahetvā nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena dhovitvā paṭisāmetabbaṃ.**When the pupil has drunk the rice porridge, the teacher should give him water and receive the vessel. Holding it low, he should wash it carefully without scratching it and then put it away.*";
P_HTM[11664]="*Antevāsikamhi vuṭṭhite āsanaṃ uddharitabbaṃ.**When the pupil has gotten up, the teacher should put away the seat.*";
P_HTM[11665]="*Sace so deso uklāpo hoti, so deso sammajjitabbo.**If the place is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11666]="*Sace antevāsiko gāmaṃ pavisitukāmo hoti, nivāsanaṃ dātabbaṃ, paṭinivāsanaṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ, kāyabandhanaṃ dātabbaṃ, saguṇaṃ katvā saṅghāṭiyo dātabbā, dhovitvā patto sodako dātabbo.**If the pupil wants to enter the village, the teacher should give him a sarong and receive the one he’s wearing in return. He should give him a belt. He should put the upper robes together, overlapping each other edge-to-edge, and then give them to him. He should wash his pupil’s bowl and give it to him while wet.*";
P_HTM[11667]="*Ettāvatā nivattissatīti āsanaṃ paññapetabbaṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ pādakathalikaṃ upanikkhipitabbaṃ, paccuggantvā pattacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ, paṭinivāsanaṃ dātabbaṃ, nivāsanaṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ.**Before he’s due back, the teacher should prepare a seat and set out a foot stool, a foot scraper, and water for washing the feet. He should go out to meet the pupil and receive his bowl and robe. He should give him a sarong and receive the one he’s wearing in return.*";
P_HTM[11668]="*Sace cīvaraṃ sinnaṃ hoti, muhuttaṃ uṇhe otāpetabbaṃ, na ca uṇhe cīvaraṃ nidahitabbaṃ.**If the robe is moist, he should sun it for a short while, but he shouldn’t leave it in the heat.*";
P_HTM[11669]="*Cīvaraṃ saṅgharitabbaṃ.**He should fold the robe,*";
P_HTM[11670]="*Cīvaraṃ saṅgharantena caturaṅgulaṃ kaṇṇaṃ ussāretvā cīvaraṃ saṅgharitabbaṃ—**offsetting the edges by seven centimeters,*";
P_HTM[11671]="*mā majjhe bhaṅgo ahosīti.**so that the fold doesn’t become worn.*";
P_HTM[11672]="*Obhoge kāyabandhanaṃ kātabbaṃ.**He should place the belt in the fold.*";
P_HTM[11673]="*Sace piṇḍapāto hoti, antevāsiko ca bhuñjitukāmo hoti, udakaṃ datvā piṇḍapāto upanāmetabbo.**If there is almsfood and his pupil wants to eat, the teacher should give him water and then the almsfood.*";
P_HTM[11674]="*Antevāsiko pānīyena pucchitabbo.**He should ask his pupil if he wants water to drink.*";
P_HTM[11675]="*Bhuttāvissa udakaṃ datvā pattaṃ paṭiggahetvā nīcaṃ katvā sādhukaṃ appaṭighaṃsantena dhovitvā vodakaṃ katvā muhuttaṃ uṇhe otāpetabbo, na ca uṇhe patto nidahitabbo.**When the pupil has eaten, the teacher should give him water and receive his bowl. Holding it low, he should wash it carefully without scratching it. He should then dry it and sun it for a short while, but he shouldn’t leave it in the heat.*";
P_HTM[11676]="*Pattacīvaraṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ.**The teacher should put away the robe and bowl.*";
P_HTM[11677]="*Pattaṃ nikkhipantena …pe…**When putting away the bowl, he should hold the bowl in one hand, feel under the bed or the bench with the other, and then put it away. He shouldn’t put the bowl away on the bare floor.*";
P_HTM[11678]="*cīvaraṃ nikkhipantena …pe…**When putting away the robe, he should hold the robe in one hand, wipe the bamboo robe rack or the clothesline with the other, and then put it away by folding the robe over it,*";
P_HTM[11679]="*pārato antaṃ orato bhogaṃ katvā cīvaraṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ.**making the ends face the wall and the fold face out.*";
P_HTM[11680]="*Antevāsikamhi uṭṭhite āsanaṃ uddharitabbaṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ pādakathalikaṃ paṭisāmetabbaṃ.**When the pupil has gotten up, the teacher should put away the seat and also the foot stool, the foot scraper, and the water for washing the feet.*";
P_HTM[11681]="*Sace so deso uklāpo hoti, so deso sammajjitabbo.**If the place is dirty, he should sweep it.*";
P_HTM[11682]="*Sace antevāsiko nahāyitukāmo hoti, nahānaṃ paṭiyādetabbaṃ.**“If the pupil wants to bathe, the teacher should prepare a bath.*";
P_HTM[11683]="*Sace sītena attho hoti, sītaṃ paṭiyādetabbaṃ.**If he wants a cold bath, he should prepare that;*";
P_HTM[11684]="*Sace uṇhena attho hoti, uṇhaṃ paṭiyādetabbaṃ.**if he wants a hot bath, he should prepare that.*";
P_HTM[11685]="*Sace antevāsiko jantāgharaṃ pavisitukāmo hoti, cuṇṇaṃ sannetabbaṃ, mattikā temetabbā, jantāgharapīṭhaṃ ādāya gantvā jantāgharapīṭhaṃ datvā cīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ, cuṇṇaṃ dātabbaṃ, mattikā dātabbā.**If the pupil wants to take a sauna, the teacher should knead bath powder, moisten the clay, take a sauna stool, and go to the sauna. After giving the pupil the sauna stool, receiving his robe, and putting it aside, he should give him the bath powder and the clay.*";
P_HTM[11686]="*Sace ussahati jantāgharaṃ pavisitabbaṃ.**If he’s able, he should enter the sauna.*";
P_HTM[11687]="*Jantāgharaṃ pavisantena mattikāya mukhaṃ makkhetvā purato ca pacchato ca paṭicchādetvā jantāgharaṃ pavisitabbaṃ.**When entering the sauna, he should smear his face with clay, cover himself front and back, and then enter.*";
P_HTM[11688]="*Na there bhikkhū anupakhajja nisīditabbaṃ.**He shouldn’t sit encroaching on the senior monks,*";
P_HTM[11689]="*Na navā bhikkhū āsanena paṭibāhitabbā.**and he shouldn’t block the junior monks from getting a seat.*";
P_HTM[11690]="*Jantāghare antevāsikassa parikammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**While in the sauna, he should do services for his pupil.*";
P_HTM[11691]="*Jantāgharā nikkhamantena jantāgharapīṭhaṃ ādāya purato ca pacchato ca paṭicchādetvā jantāgharā nikkhamitabbaṃ.**When leaving the sauna, he should take the sauna stool, cover himself front and back, and then leave.*";
P_HTM[11692]="*Udakepi antevāsikassa parikammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**The teacher should also do services for his pupil in the water.*";
P_HTM[11693]="*Nahātena paṭhamataraṃ uttaritvā attano gattaṃ vodakaṃ katvā nivāsetvā antevāsikassa gattato udakaṃ pamajjitabbaṃ, nivāsanaṃ dātabbaṃ, saṅghāṭi dātabbā, jantāgharapīṭhaṃ ādāya paṭhamataraṃ āgantvā āsanaṃ paññapetabbaṃ, pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ pādakathalikaṃ upanikkhipitabbaṃ, antevāsiko pānīyena pucchitabbo.**When the teacher has bathed, he should be the first to come out. He should dry himself and put on his sarong. He should then wipe the water off his pupil’s body, and he should give him his sarong and then his upper robe. Taking the sauna stool, he should be the first to return. He should prepare a seat, and also set out a foot stool, a foot scraper, and water for washing the feet. He should ask his pupil if he wants water to drink.*";
P_HTM[11694]="*Yasmiṃ vihāre antevāsiko viharati, sace so vihāro uklāpo hoti, sace ussahati, sodhetabbo.**“If the dwelling where the pupil is staying is dirty, the teacher should clean it if he’s able.*";
P_HTM[11695]="*Vihāraṃ sodhentena paṭhamaṃ pattacīvaraṃ nīharitvā ekamantaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ …pe…**When he’s cleaning the dwelling, he should first take out the bowl and robe and put them aside. He should take out the sitting mat and the sheet and put them aside. He should take out the mattress and the pillow and put them aside. Holding the bed low, he should carefully take it out without scratching it or knocking it against the door or the door frame, and he should put it aside. Holding the bench low, he should carefully take it out without scratching it or knocking it against the door or the door frame, and he should put it aside. He should take out the bed supports and put them aside. He should take out the spittoon and put it aside. He should take out the leaning board and put it aside. After taking note of its position, he should take out the floor cover and put it aside. If the dwelling has cobwebs, he should first remove them from the ceiling cloth, and he should then sweep the windows and the corners of the room. If the walls have been treated with red ocher and they’re moldy, he should moisten a cloth, wring it out, and wipe the walls. If the floor has been treated with a black finish and it’s moldy, he should moisten a cloth, wring it out, and wipe the floor. If the floor is untreated, he should sprinkle it with water and then sweep it, while trying to avoid stirring up dust. He should look out for any trash and discard it.*";
P_HTM[11696]="*He should sun the floor cover, clean it, beat it, bring it back inside, and put it back as before. He should sun the bed supports, wipe them, bring them back inside, and place them in the same position as before. He should sun the bed, clean it, and beat it. Holding it low, he should carefully bring it back inside without scratching it or knocking it against the door or the door frame, and he should put it back in the same place as before. He should sun the bench, clean it, and beat it. Holding it low, he should carefully bring it back inside without scratching it or knocking it against the door or the door frame, and he should put it back in the same place as before. He should sun the mattress and the pillow, clean them, beat them, bring them back inside, and put them back as before. He should sun the sitting mat and the sheet, clean them, beat them, bring them back inside, and put them back as before. He should sun the spittoon, wipe it, bring it back inside, and put it back where it was. He should sun the reclining board, wipe it, bring it back inside, and put it back where it was. He should put away the bowl and robe. When putting away the bowl, he should hold the bowl in one hand, feel under the bed or the bench with the other, and then put it away. He shouldn’t put the bowl away on the bare floor. When putting away the robe, he should hold the robe in one hand, wipe the bamboo robe rack or the clothesline with the other, and then put it away by folding the robe over it, making the ends face the wall and the fold face out.* **";
P_HTM[11697]="*If dusty winds are blowing from the east, he should close the windows on the eastern side. If dusty winds are blowing from the west, he should close the windows on the western side. If dusty winds are blowing from the north, he should close the windows on the northern side. If dusty winds are blowing from the south, he should close the windows on the southern side. If the weather is cold, he should open the windows during the day and close them at night. If the weather is hot, he should close the windows during the day and open them at night.* **";
P_HTM[11698]="*If the precincts are dirty, he should sweep them. If the gateway is dirty, he should sweep it. If the assembly hall is dirty, he should sweep it. If the water-boiling shed is dirty, he should sweep it. If the restroom is dirty, he should sweep it. If there is no water for drinking, he should get some. If there is no water for washing, he should get some.* **";
P_HTM[11699]="*ācamanakumbhiyā udakaṃ na hoti, ācamanakumbhiyā udakaṃ āsiñcitabbaṃ.**If there is no water in the rinsing pot, he should fill it.*";
P_HTM[11700]="*Sace antevāsikassa anabhirati uppannā hoti, ācariyena vūpakāsetabbo, vūpakāsāpetabbo, dhammakathā vāssa kātabbā.**“If the pupil becomes discontent with the spiritual life, the teacher should send him away or have him sent away, or he should give him a teaching.*";
P_HTM[11701]="*Sace antevāsikassa kukkuccaṃ uppannaṃ hoti, ācariyena vinodetabbaṃ, vinodāpetabbaṃ, dhammakathā vāssa kātabbā.**If the pupil becomes anxious, the teacher should dispel it or have it dispelled, or he should give him a teaching.*";
P_HTM[11702]="*Sace antevāsikassa diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ hoti, ācariyena vivecetabbaṃ, vivecāpetabbaṃ, dhammakathā vāssa kātabbā.**If the pupil has a wrong view, the teacher should make him give it up or have someone else do it, or he should give him a teaching.*";
P_HTM[11703]="*Sace antevāsiko garudhammaṃ ajjhāpanno hoti, parivāsāraho, ācariyena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**If the pupil has committed a heavy offense and deserves probation,*";
P_HTM[11704]="*kinti nu kho saṅgho antevāsikassa parivāsaṃ dadeyyāti.**the teacher should try to get the Sangha to give it to him.*";
P_HTM[11705]="*Sace antevāsiko mūlāyapaṭikassanāraho hoti, ācariyena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**If the pupil has committed a heavy offense and deserves to be sent back to the beginning,*";
P_HTM[11706]="*kinti nu kho saṅgho antevāsikaṃ mūlāya paṭikasseyyāti.**the teacher should try to get the Sangha to do it.*";
P_HTM[11707]="*Sace antevāsiko mānattāraho hoti, ācariyena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**If the pupil has committed a heavy offense and deserves the trial period,*";
P_HTM[11708]="*kinti nu kho saṅgho antevāsikassa mānattaṃ dadeyyāti.**the teacher should try to get the Sangha to give it to him.*";
P_HTM[11709]="*Sace antevāsiko abbhānāraho hoti, ācariyena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**If the pupil has committed a heavy offense and deserves rehabilitation,*";
P_HTM[11710]="*kinti nu kho saṅgho antevāsikaṃ abbheyyāti.**the teacher should try to get the Sangha to give it to him.*";
P_HTM[11711]="*Sace saṅgho antevāsikassa kammaṃ kattukāmo hoti, tajjanīyaṃ vā niyassaṃ vā pabbājanīyaṃ vā paṭisāraṇīyaṃ vā ukkhepanīyaṃ vā, ācariyena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**If the Sangha wants to do a legal procedure against his pupil—whether a procedure of condemnation, demotion, banishment, reconciliation, or ejection—*";
P_HTM[11712]="*kinti nu kho saṅgho antevāsikassa kammaṃ na kareyya, lahukāya vā pariṇāmeyyāti.**the teacher should make an effort to stop it or to reduce the penalty.*";
P_HTM[11713]="*Kataṃ vā panassa hoti, saṅghena kammaṃ, tajjanīyaṃ vā niyassaṃ vā pabbājanīyaṃ vā paṭisāraṇīyaṃ vā ukkhepanīyaṃ vā, ācariyena ussukkaṃ kātabbaṃ—**But if the Sangha has already done a legal procedure against his pupil—whether a procedure of condemnation, demotion, banishment, reconciliation, or ejection—*";
P_HTM[11714]="*kinti nu kho antevāsiko sammā vatteyya, lomaṃ pāteyya, netthāraṃ vatteyya, saṅgho taṃ kammaṃ paṭippassambheyyāti.**the teacher should help the pupil conduct himself properly and suitably so as to deserve to be released, and try to get the Sangha to lift that procedure.*";
P_HTM[11715]="*Sace antevāsikassa cīvaraṃ dhovitabbaṃ hoti, ācariyena ācikkhitabbaṃ—evaṃ dhoveyyāsīti,**“If the pupil’s robe needs washing, the teacher should show him how to do it,*";
P_HTM[11716]="*ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—kinti nu kho antevāsikassa cīvaraṃ dhoviyethāti.**or he should make an effort to get it done.*";
P_HTM[11717]="*Sace antevāsikassa cīvaraṃ kātabbaṃ hoti, ācariyena ācikkhitabbaṃ—evaṃ kareyyāsīti,**If the pupil needs a robe, the teacher should show him how to make one,*";
P_HTM[11718]="*ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—kinti nu kho antevāsikassa cīvaraṃ kariyethāti.**or he should make an effort to get one made.*";
P_HTM[11719]="*Sace antevāsikassa rajanaṃ pacitabbaṃ hoti, ācariyena ācikkhitabbaṃ—evaṃ paceyyāsīti,**If the pupil needs dye, the teacher should show him how to make it,*";
P_HTM[11720]="*ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—kinti nu kho antevāsikassa rajanaṃ paciyethāti.**or he should make an effort to get it made.*";
P_HTM[11721]="*Sace antevāsikassa cīvaraṃ rajitabbaṃ hoti, ācariyena ācikkhitabbaṃ—evaṃ rajeyyāsīti,**If the pupil’s robe needs dyeing, the teacher should show him how to do it,*";
P_HTM[11722]="*ussukkaṃ vā kātabbaṃ—kinti nu kho antevāsikassa cīvaraṃ rajiyethāti.**or he should make an effort to get it done.*";
P_HTM[11723]="*Cīvaraṃ rajantena sādhukaṃ samparivattakaṃ samparivattakaṃ rajitabbaṃ.**When he’s dyeing the robe, he should carefully and repeatedly turn it over,*";
P_HTM[11724]="*Na ca acchinne theve pakkamitabbaṃ.**and he shouldn’t go away while it’s still dripping.*";
P_HTM[11725]="*Sace antevāsiko gilāno hoti, yāvajīvaṃ upaṭṭhātabbo, vuṭṭhānamassa āgametabbaṃ.**If his pupil is sick, he should nurse him for as long as he lives, or he should wait until he has recovered.*";
P_HTM[11726]="*Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, ācariyānaṃ antevāsikesu vattaṃ yathā ācariyehi antevāsikesu sammā vattitabban”ti.**This is the proper conduct of a teacher toward his pupil.”*";
P_HTM[11727]="*Vattakkhandhako aṭṭhamo. Imamhi khandhake vatthū ekūnavīsati, vattā cuddasa.**The eighth chapter on proper conduct is finished. In this chapter there are nineteen topics and fourteen kinds of proper conduct.*";
P_HTM[11728]="*Tassuddānaṃ* **";
P_HTM[11729]="*Saupāhanā chattā ca,* **";
P_HTM[11730]="*oguṇṭhi sīsaṃ pānīyaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11731]="*Nābhivāde na pucchanti,* **";
P_HTM[11732]="*ahi ujjhanti pesalā.* **";
P_HTM[11733]="*Omuñci chattaṃ khandhe ca,* **";
P_HTM[11734]="*atarañca paṭikkamaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11735]="*Pattacīvaraṃ nikkhipā,* **";
P_HTM[11736]="*patirūpañca pucchitā.* **";
P_HTM[11737]="*Āsiñceyya dhovitena,* **";
P_HTM[11738]="*sukkhenallenupāhanā;* **";
P_HTM[11739]="*Vuḍḍho navako puccheyya,* **";
P_HTM[11740]="*ajjhāvuṭṭhañca gocarā.* **";
P_HTM[11741]="*Sekkhā vaccā pānī pari,* **";
P_HTM[11742]="*kattaraṃ katikaṃ tato;* **";
P_HTM[11743]="*Kālaṃ muhuttaṃ uklāpo,* **";
P_HTM[11744]="*bhūmattharaṇaṃ nīhare.* **";
P_HTM[11745]="*Paṭipādo bhisibibbo,* **";
P_HTM[11746]="*mañcapīṭhañca mallakaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11747]="*Apassenullokakaṇṇā,* **";
P_HTM[11748]="*gerukā kāḷa akatā.* **";
P_HTM[11749]="*Saṅkārañca bhūmattharaṇaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11750]="*paṭipādakaṃ mañcapīṭhaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11751]="*Bhisi nisīdanampi,* **";
P_HTM[11752]="*mallakaṃ apassena ca.* **";
P_HTM[11753]="*Pattacīvaraṃ bhūmi ca,* **";
P_HTM[11754]="*pārantaṃ orato bhogaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11755]="*Puratthimā pacchimā ca,* **";
P_HTM[11756]="*uttarā atha dakkhiṇā.* **";
P_HTM[11757]="*Sītuṇhe ca divārattiṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11758]="*pariveṇañca koṭṭhako;* **";
P_HTM[11759]="*Upaṭṭhānaggi sālā ca,* **";
P_HTM[11760]="*vattaṃ vaccakuṭīsu ca.* **";
P_HTM[11761]="*Pānī paribhojaniyā,* **";
P_HTM[11762]="*kumbhi ācamanesu ca;* **";
P_HTM[11763]="*Anopamena paññattaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11764]="*vattaṃ āgantukehime.* **";
P_HTM[11765]="*Nevāsanaṃ na udakaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11766]="*na paccu na ca pāniyaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11767]="*Nābhivāde na paññape,* **";
P_HTM[11768]="*ujjhāyanti ca pesalā.* **";
P_HTM[11769]="*Vuḍḍhāsanañca udakaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11770]="*paccuggantvā ca pāniyaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11771]="*Upāhane ekamantaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11772]="*abhivāde ca paññape.* **";
P_HTM[11773]="*Vutthaṃ gocarasekkho ca,* **";
P_HTM[11774]="*ṭhānaṃ pāniyabhojanaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11775]="*Kattaraṃ katikaṃ kālaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11776]="*navakassa nisinnake.* **";
P_HTM[11777]="*Abhivādaye ācikkhe,* **";
P_HTM[11778]="*yathā heṭṭhā tathā naye;* **";
P_HTM[11779]="*Niddiṭṭhaṃ satthavāhena,* **";
P_HTM[11780]="*vattaṃ āvāsikehime.* **";
P_HTM[11781]="*Gamikā dārumatti ca,* **";
P_HTM[11782]="*vivaritvā na pucchiya;* **";
P_HTM[11783]="*Nassanti ca aguttañca,* **";
P_HTM[11784]="*ujjhāyanti ca pesalā.* **";
P_HTM[11785]="*Paṭisāmetvā thaketvā,* **";
P_HTM[11786]="*āpucchitvāva pakkame;* **";
P_HTM[11787]="*Bhikkhu vā sāmaṇero vā,* **";
P_HTM[11788]="*ārāmiko upāsako.* **";
P_HTM[11789]="*Pāsāṇakesu ca puñjaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11790]="*paṭisāme thakeyya ca;* **";
P_HTM[11791]="*Sace ussahati ussukkaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11792]="*anovasse tatheva ca.* **";
P_HTM[11793]="*Sabbo ovassati gāmaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11794]="*ajjhokāse tatheva ca;* **";
P_HTM[11795]="*Appevaṅgāni seseyyuṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11796]="*vattaṃ gamikabhikkhunā.* **";
P_HTM[11797]="*Nānumodanti therena,* **";
P_HTM[11798]="*ohāya catupañcahi;* **";
P_HTM[11799]="*Vaccito mucchito āsi,* **";
P_HTM[11800]="*vattānumodanesume.* **";
P_HTM[11801]="*Chabbaggiyā dunnivatthā,* **";
P_HTM[11802]="*athopi ca duppārutā;* **";
P_HTM[11803]="*Anākappā ca vokkamma,* **";
P_HTM[11804]="*there anupakhajjane.* **";
P_HTM[11805]="*Nave bhikkhū ca saṅghāṭi,* **";
P_HTM[11806]="*ujjhāyanti ca pesalā;* **";
P_HTM[11807]="*Timaṇḍalaṃ nivāsetvā,* **";
P_HTM[11808]="*kāyasaguṇagaṇṭhikā.* **";
P_HTM[11809]="*Na vokkamma paṭicchannaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11810]="*susaṃvutokkhittacakkhu;* **";
P_HTM[11811]="*Ukkhittojjagghikāsaddo,* **";
P_HTM[11812]="*tayo ceva pacālanā.* **";
P_HTM[11813]="*Khambhoguṇṭhiukkuṭikā,* **";
P_HTM[11814]="*paṭicchannaṃ susaṃvuto;* **";
P_HTM[11815]="*Okkhittukkhittaujjagghi,* **";
P_HTM[11816]="*appasaddo tayo calā.* **";
P_HTM[11817]="*Khambhoguṇṭhipallatthi ca,* **";
P_HTM[11818]="*anupakhajja nāsane;* **";
P_HTM[11819]="*Ottharitvāna udake,* **";
P_HTM[11820]="*nīcaṃ katvāna siñciyā.* **";
P_HTM[11821]="*Paṭi sāmantā saṅghāṭi,* **";
P_HTM[11822]="*odane ca paṭiggahe;* **";
P_HTM[11823]="*Sūpaṃ uttaribhaṅgena,* **";
P_HTM[11824]="*sabbesaṃ samatitthi ca.* **";
P_HTM[11825]="*Sakkaccaṃ pattasaññī ca,* **";
P_HTM[11826]="*sapadānañca sūpakaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11827]="*Na thūpato paṭicchāde,* **";
P_HTM[11828]="*viññattujjhānasaññinā.* **";
P_HTM[11829]="*Mahantamaṇḍaladvāraṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11830]="*sabbahattho na byāhare;* **";
P_HTM[11831]="*Ukkhepo chedanāgaṇḍa,* **";
P_HTM[11832]="*dhunaṃ sitthāvakārakaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11833]="*Jivhānicchārakañceva,* **";
P_HTM[11834]="*capucapu surusuru;* **";
P_HTM[11835]="*Hatthapattoṭṭhanillehaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11836]="*sāmisena paṭiggahe.* **";
P_HTM[11837]="*Yāva na sabbe udake,* **";
P_HTM[11838]="*nīcaṃ katvāna siñciyaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11839]="*Paṭi sāmantā saṅghāṭi,* **";
P_HTM[11840]="*nīcaṃ katvā chamāya ca.* **";
P_HTM[11841]="*Sasitthakaṃ nivattante,* **";
P_HTM[11842]="*suppaṭicchannamukkuṭi;* **";
P_HTM[11843]="*Dhammarājena paññattaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11844]="*idaṃ bhattaggavattanaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11845]="*Dunnivatthā anākappā,* **";
P_HTM[11846]="*asallakkhetvā ca sahasā;* **";
P_HTM[11847]="*Dūre acca ciraṃ lahuṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11848]="*tatheva piṇḍacāriko.* **";
P_HTM[11849]="*Paṭicchannova gaccheyya,* **";
P_HTM[11850]="*susaṃvutokkhittacakkhu;* **";
P_HTM[11851]="*Ukkhittojjagghikāsaddo,* **";
P_HTM[11852]="*tayo ceva pacālanā.* **";
P_HTM[11853]="*Khambhoguṇṭhiukkuṭikā,* **";
P_HTM[11854]="*sallakkhetvā ca sahasā;* **";
P_HTM[11855]="*Dūre acca ciraṃ lahuṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11856]="*āsanakaṃ kaṭacchukā.* **";
P_HTM[11857]="*Bhājanaṃ vā ṭhapeti ca,* **";
P_HTM[11858]="*uccāretvā paṇāmetvā;* **";
P_HTM[11859]="*Paṭiggahe na ulloke,* **";
P_HTM[11860]="*sūpesupi tatheva taṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11861]="*Bhikkhu saṅghāṭiyā chāde,* **";
P_HTM[11862]="*paṭicchanneva gacchiyaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11863]="*Saṃvutokkhittacakkhu ca,* **";
P_HTM[11864]="*ukkhittojjagghikāya ca;* **";
P_HTM[11865]="*Appasaddo tayo cālā,* **";
P_HTM[11866]="*khambhoguṇṭhikaukkuṭi.* **";
P_HTM[11867]="*Paṭhamāsanavakkāra,* **";
P_HTM[11868]="*pāniyaṃ paribhojanī;* **";
P_HTM[11869]="*Pacchākaṅkhati bhuñjeyya,* **";
P_HTM[11870]="*opilāpeyya uddhare.* **";
P_HTM[11871]="*Paṭisāmeyya sammajje,* **";
P_HTM[11872]="*rittaṃ tucchaṃ upaṭṭhape;* **";
P_HTM[11873]="*Hatthavikāre bhindeyya,* **";
P_HTM[11874]="*vattidaṃ piṇḍacārike.* **";
P_HTM[11875]="*Pānī pari aggiraṇi,* **";
P_HTM[11876]="*nakkhattadisacorā ca;* **";
P_HTM[11877]="*Sabbaṃ natthīti koṭṭetvā,* **";
P_HTM[11878]="*pattaṃse cīvaraṃ tato.* **";
P_HTM[11879]="*Idāni aṃse laggetvā,* **";
P_HTM[11880]="*timaṇḍalaṃ parimaṇḍalaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11881]="*Yathā piṇḍacārivattaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11882]="*naye āraññakesupi.* **";
P_HTM[11883]="*Pattaṃse cīvaraṃ sīse,* **";
P_HTM[11884]="*ārohitvā ca pāniyaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11885]="*Paribhojaniyaṃ aggi,* **";
P_HTM[11886]="*araṇī cāpi kattaraṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11887]="*Nakkhattaṃ sappadesaṃ vā,* **";
P_HTM[11888]="*disāpi kusalo bhave;* **";
P_HTM[11889]="*Sattuttamena paññattaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11890]="*vattaṃ āraññakesume.* **";
P_HTM[11891]="*Ajjhokāse okiriṃsu,* **";
P_HTM[11892]="*ujjhāyanti ca pesalā;* **";
P_HTM[11893]="*Sace vihāro uklāpo,* **";
P_HTM[11894]="*paṭhamaṃ pattacīvaraṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11895]="*Bhisibibbohanaṃ mañcaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11896]="*pīṭhañca kheḷamallakaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11897]="*Apassenullokakaṇṇā,* **";
P_HTM[11898]="*gerukā kāḷa akatā.* **";
P_HTM[11899]="*Saṅkāraṃ bhikkhusāmantā,* **";
P_HTM[11900]="*senāvihārapāniyaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11901]="*Paribhojanasāmantā,* **";
P_HTM[11902]="*paṭivāte ca aṅgaṇe.* **";
P_HTM[11903]="*Adhovāte attharaṇaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11904]="*paṭipādakamañco ca;* **";
P_HTM[11905]="*Pīṭhaṃ bhisi nisīdanaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11906]="*mallakaṃ apassena ca.* **";
P_HTM[11907]="*Pattacīvaraṃ bhūmi ca,* **";
P_HTM[11908]="*pārantaṃ orato bhogaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11909]="*Puratthimā ca pacchimā,* **";
P_HTM[11910]="*uttarā atha dakkhiṇā.* **";
P_HTM[11911]="*Sītuṇhe ca divā rattiṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11912]="*pariveṇañca koṭṭhako;* **";
P_HTM[11913]="*Upaṭṭhānaggisālā ca,* **";
P_HTM[11914]="*vaccakuṭī ca pāniyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11915]="*Ācamanakumbhi vuḍḍhe ca,* **";
P_HTM[11916]="*uddesapucchanā sajjhā;* **";
P_HTM[11917]="*Dhammo padīpaṃ vijjhāpe,* **";
P_HTM[11918]="*na vivare napi thake.* **";
P_HTM[11919]="*Yena vuḍḍho parivatti,* **";
P_HTM[11920]="*kaṇṇenapi na ghaṭṭaye;* **";
P_HTM[11921]="*Paññapesi mahāvīro,* **";
P_HTM[11922]="*vattaṃ senāsanesu taṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11923]="*Nivāriyamānā dvāraṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11924]="*mucchitujjhanti pesalā;* **";
P_HTM[11925]="*Chārikaṃ chaḍḍaye jantā,* **";
P_HTM[11926]="*paribhaṇḍaṃ tatheva ca.* **";
P_HTM[11927]="*Pariveṇaṃ koṭṭhako sālā,* **";
P_HTM[11928]="*cuṇṇamattikadoṇikā;* **";
P_HTM[11929]="*Mukhaṃ purato na there,* **";
P_HTM[11930]="*na nave ussahati sace.* **";
P_HTM[11931]="*Purato uparimaggo,* **";
P_HTM[11932]="*cikkhallaṃ matti pīṭhakaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11933]="*Vijjhāpetvā thaketvā ca,* **";
P_HTM[11934]="*vattaṃ jantāgharesume.* **";
P_HTM[11935]="*Nācameti yathāvuḍḍhaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11936]="*paṭipāṭi ca sahasā;* **";
P_HTM[11937]="*Ubbhaji nitthuno kaṭṭhaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11938]="*vaccaṃ passāva kheḷakaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11939]="*Pharusā kūpa sahasā,* **";
P_HTM[11940]="*ubbhaji capu sesena;* **";
P_HTM[11941]="*Bahi anto ca ukkāse,* **";
P_HTM[11942]="*rajju ataramānañca.* **";
P_HTM[11943]="*Sahasā ubbhaji ṭhite,* **";
P_HTM[11944]="*nitthune kaṭṭha vaccañca;* **";
P_HTM[11945]="*Passāva kheḷa pharusā,* **";
P_HTM[11946]="*kūpañca vaccapāduke.* **";
P_HTM[11947]="*Nātisahasā ubbhaji,* **";
P_HTM[11948]="*pādukāya capucapu;* **";
P_HTM[11949]="*Na sesaye paṭicchāde,* **";
P_HTM[11950]="*uhatapidharena ca.* **";
P_HTM[11951]="*Vaccakuṭī paribhaṇḍaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11952]="*pariveṇañca koṭṭhako;* **";
P_HTM[11953]="*Ācamane ca udakaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11954]="*vattaṃ vaccakuṭīsume.* **";
P_HTM[11955]="*Upāhanā dantakaṭṭhaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11956]="*mukhodakañca āsanaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11957]="*Yāgu udakaṃ dhovitvā,* **";
P_HTM[11958]="*uddhāruklāpa gāma ca.* **";
P_HTM[11959]="*Nivāsanā kāyabandhā,* **";
P_HTM[11960]="*saguṇaṃ pattasodakaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11961]="*Pacchā timaṇḍalo ceva,* **";
P_HTM[11962]="*parimaṇḍala bandhanaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11963]="*Saguṇaṃ dhovitvā pacchā,* **";
P_HTM[11964]="*nātidūre paṭiggahe;* **";
P_HTM[11965]="*Bhaṇamānassa āpatti,* **";
P_HTM[11966]="*paṭhamāgantvāna āsanaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11967]="*Udakaṃ pīṭhakathali,* **";
P_HTM[11968]="*paccuggantvā nivāsanaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11969]="*Otāpe nidahi bhaṅgo,* **";
P_HTM[11970]="*obhoge bhuñjitu name.* **";
P_HTM[11971]="*Pānīyaṃ udakaṃ nīcaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11972]="*muhuttaṃ na ca nidahe;* **";
P_HTM[11973]="*Pattacīvaraṃ bhūmi ca,* **";
P_HTM[11974]="*pārantaṃ orato bhogaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11975]="*Uddhare paṭisāme ca,* **";
P_HTM[11976]="*uklāpo ca nahāyituṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11977]="*Sītaṃ uṇhaṃ jantāgharaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11978]="*cuṇṇaṃ mattika piṭṭhito.* **";
P_HTM[11979]="*Pīṭhañca cīvaraṃ cuṇṇaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11980]="*mattikussahati mukhaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11981]="*Purato there nave ca,* **";
P_HTM[11982]="*parikammañca nikkhame.* **";
P_HTM[11983]="*Purato udake nhāte,* **";
P_HTM[11984]="*nivāsetvā upajjhāyaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[11985]="*Nivāsanañca saṅghāṭi,* **";
P_HTM[11986]="*pīṭhakaṃ āsanena ca.* **";
P_HTM[11987]="*Pādo pīṭhaṃ kathaliñca,* **";
P_HTM[11988]="*pānīyuddesapucchanā;* **";
P_HTM[11989]="*Uklāpaṃ susodheyya,* **";
P_HTM[11990]="*paṭhamaṃ pattacīvaraṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11991]="*Nisīdanapaccattharaṇaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11992]="*bhisi bibbohanāni ca;* **";
P_HTM[11993]="*Mañco pīṭhaṃ paṭipādaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[11994]="*mallakaṃ apassena ca.* **";
P_HTM[11995]="*Bhūma santāna āloka,* **";
P_HTM[11996]="*gerukā kāḷa akatā;* **";
P_HTM[11997]="*Bhūmattharapaṭipādā,* **";
P_HTM[11998]="*mañco pīṭhaṃ bibbohanaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[11999]="*Nisīdattharaṇaṃ kheḷa,* **";
P_HTM[12000]="*apasse pattacīvaraṃ;* **";
P_HTM[12001]="*Puratthimā pacchimā ca,* **";
P_HTM[12002]="*uttarā atha dakkhiṇā.* **";
P_HTM[12003]="*Sītuṇhañca divā rattiṃ,* **";
P_HTM[12004]="*pariveṇañca koṭṭhako;* **";
P_HTM[12005]="*Upaṭṭhānaggisālā ca,* **";
P_HTM[12006]="*vaccapāniyabhojanī.* **";
P_HTM[12007]="*Ācamaṃ anabhirati,* **";
P_HTM[12008]="*kukkuccaṃ diṭṭhi ca garu;* **";
P_HTM[12009]="*Mūlamānattaabbhānaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[12010]="*tajjanīyaṃ niyassakaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[12011]="*Pabbāja paṭisāraṇī,* **";
P_HTM[12012]="*ukkhepañca kataṃ yadi;* **";
P_HTM[12013]="*Dhove kātabbaṃ rajañca,* **";
P_HTM[12014]="*raje samparivattakaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[12015]="*Pattañca cīvarañcāpi,* **";
P_HTM[12016]="*parikkhārañca chedanaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[12017]="*Parikammaṃ veyyāvaccaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[12018]="*pacchā piṇḍaṃ pavisanaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[12019]="*Na susānaṃ disā ceva,* **";
P_HTM[12020]="*yāvajīvaṃ upaṭṭhahe;* **";
P_HTM[12021]="*Saddhivihārikenetaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[12022]="*vattupajjhāyakesume.* **";
P_HTM[12023]="*Ovādasāsanuddesā,* **";
P_HTM[12024]="*pucchā pattañca cīvaraṃ;* **";
P_HTM[12025]="*Parikkhāro gilāno ca,* **";
P_HTM[12026]="*na pacchāsamaṇo bhave.* **";
P_HTM[12027]="*Upajjhāyesu ye vattā,* **";
P_HTM[12028]="*evaṃ ācariyesupi;* **";
P_HTM[12029]="*Saddhivihārike vattā,* **";
P_HTM[12030]="*tatheva antevāsike.* **";
P_HTM[12031]="*Āgantukesu ye vattā,* **";
P_HTM[12032]="*puna āvāsikesu ca;* **";
P_HTM[12033]="*Gamikānumodanikā,* **";
P_HTM[12034]="*bhattagge piṇḍacārike.* **";
P_HTM[12035]="*Āraññakesu yaṃ vattaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[12036]="*yañca senāsanesupi;* **";
P_HTM[12037]="*Jantāghare vaccakuṭī,* **";
P_HTM[12038]="*upajjhā saddhivihārike.* **";
P_HTM[12039]="*Ācariyesu yaṃ vattaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[12040]="*tatheva antevāsike;* **";
P_HTM[12041]="*Ekūnavīsati vatthū,* **";
P_HTM[12042]="*vattā cuddasa khandhake.* **";
P_HTM[12043]="*Vattaṃ aparipūrento,**If you do not fulfill the proper conduct,*";
P_HTM[12044]="*na sīlaṃ paripūrati;**Then you do not fulfill your virtue.*";
P_HTM[12045]="*Asuddhasīlo duppañño,**If your virtue is impure, you are weak in wisdom;*";
P_HTM[12046]="*cittekaggaṃ na vindati.**And you do not know the unity of mind.*";
P_HTM[12047]="*Vikkhittacittonekaggo,**A mind distracted, not unified,*";
P_HTM[12048]="*sammā dhammaṃ na passati;**Does not see the truth of nature.*";
P_HTM[12049]="*Apassamāno saddhammaṃ,**Not seeing the truth of nature,*";
P_HTM[12050]="*dukkhā na parimuccati.**You are not released from suffering.*";
P_HTM[12051]="*Yaṃ vattaṃ paripūrento,**But if you do fulfill the proper conduct,*";
P_HTM[12052]="*sīlampi paripūrati;**Then you also fulfill your virtue.*";
P_HTM[12053]="*Visuddhasīlo sappañño,**If your virtue is pure, you are possessed of wisdom;*";
P_HTM[12054]="*cittekaggampi vindati.**And you know the unity of mind.*";
P_HTM[12055]="*Avikkhittacitto ekaggo,**A non-distracted mind, unified,*";
P_HTM[12056]="*sammā dhammaṃ vipassati;**Sees the truth of nature.*";
P_HTM[12057]="*Sampassamāno saddhammaṃ,**Seeing the truth of nature,*";
P_HTM[12058]="*dukkhā so parimuccati.**You are released from suffering.*";
P_HTM[12059]="*Tasmā hi vattaṃ pūreyya,**So, fulfill the proper conduct,*";
P_HTM[12060]="*jinaputto vicakkhaṇo;**you the Son of the Conqueror, possessed of insight.*";
P_HTM[12061]="*Ovādaṃ buddhaseṭṭhassa,**The instruction of the Buddha, the best—*";
P_HTM[12062]="*tato nibbānamehitīti.**Go from that to extinguishment, in this way.*";
P_HTM[12063]="*Vattakkhandhako niṭṭhito.**The chapter on proper conduct is finished.*";
P_HTM[12064]="*9. Pātimokkhaṭṭhapanakkhandhaka **9.  The chapter on the cancellation of the Monastic Code *";
P_HTM[12065]="*1. Pātimokkhuddesayācana**1. The request for the recitation of the Monastic Code*";
P_HTM[12066]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati pubbārāme migāramātu pāsāde.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Eastern Monastery, in Migāramāta’s stilt house.*";
P_HTM[12067]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā tadahuposathe bhikkhusaṅghaparivuto nisinno hoti.**On one occasion on the observance day, he was seated surrounded by the Sangha of monks.*";
P_HTM[12068]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando abhikkantāya rattiyā nikkhante paṭhame yāme uṭṭhāyāsanā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**Then, when the night was well advanced and the first part of the night was over, Venerable Ānanda got up from his seat, put his upper robe over one shoulder, raise his joined palms, and said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[12069]="*“abhikkantā, bhante, ratti, nikkhanto paṭhamo yāmo, ciranisinno bhikkhusaṅgho.**“Venerable Sir, the night is well advanced and the first part of the night is over. The Sangha of monks has been seated for a long time.*";
P_HTM[12070]="*Uddisatu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhūnaṃ pātimokkhan”ti.**Please recite the Monastic Code.”*";
P_HTM[12071]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā tuṇhī ahosi.**But the Buddha did not reply.*";
P_HTM[12072]="*Dutiyampi kho āyasmā ānando abhikkantāya rattiyā nikkhante majjhime yāme uṭṭhāyāsanā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**At the end of the middle part of the night, Venerable Ānanda asked a second time,*";
P_HTM[12073]="*“abhikkantā, bhante, ratti, nikkhanto majjhimo yāmo, ciranisinno bhikkhusaṅgho.* **";
P_HTM[12074]="*Uddisatu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhūnaṃ pātimokkhan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[12075]="*Dutiyampi kho bhagavā tuṇhī ahosi.**and again received no reply.*";
P_HTM[12076]="*Tatiyampi kho āyasmā ānando abhikkantāya rattiyā nikkhante pacchime yāme uddhaste aruṇe nandimukhiyā rattiyā uṭṭhāyāsanā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**At the end of the last part of the night, when the sky was flaring up at dawn, he asked a third time.*";
P_HTM[12077]="*“abhikkantā, bhante, ratti, nikkhanto pacchimo yāmo, uddhastaṃ aruṇaṃ nandimukhi ratti, ciranisinno bhikkhusaṅgho.* **";
P_HTM[12078]="*Uddisatu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhūnaṃ pātimokkhan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[12079]="*“Aparisuddhā, ānanda, parisā”ti.**And the Buddha replied, “Ānanda, the gathering is impure.”*";
P_HTM[12080]="*Atha kho āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa etadahosi—**Venerable Mahāmoggallāna thought,*";
P_HTM[12081]="*“kaṃ nu kho bhagavā puggalaṃ sandhāya evamāha—**“Who is the Buddha talking about?”*";
P_HTM[12082]="*‘aparisuddhā, ānanda, parisā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[12083]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno sabbāvantaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ cetasā ceto paricca manasākāsi.**He then read the minds of the the entire Sangha of monks.*";
P_HTM[12084]="*Addasā kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno taṃ puggalaṃ dussīlaṃ pāpadhammaṃ asucisaṅkassarasamācāraṃ paṭicchannakammantaṃ assamaṇaṃ samaṇapaṭiññaṃ abrahmacāriṃ brahmacāripaṭiññaṃ antopūtiṃ avassutaṃ kasambujātaṃ majjhe bhikkhusaṅghassa nisinnaṃ.**And he saw that person—immoral, with bad qualities, impure and dubious in conduct, hiding his actions, not a monastic while claiming to be one, not abstaining from sexuality while claiming to do so, rotten inside, lustful, defiled—seated in the midst of the Sangha of monks.*";
P_HTM[12085]="*Disvāna yena so puggalo tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā taṃ puggalaṃ etadavoca—**He went up to him and said,*";
P_HTM[12086]="*“uṭṭhehi, āvuso, diṭṭhosi bhagavatā;**“Get up, the Buddha has seen you.*";
P_HTM[12087]="*natthi te bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ saṃvāso”ti.**You don’t belong to the community of monks.”*";
P_HTM[12088]="*Evaṃ vutte, so puggalo tuṇhī ahosi.**But he did not reply.*";
P_HTM[12089]="*Dutiyampi kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno taṃ puggalaṃ etadavoca—**Mahāmoggallāna said the same thing a second*";
P_HTM[12090]="*“uṭṭhehi, āvuso, diṭṭhosi bhagavatā;* **";
P_HTM[12091]="*natthi te bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ saṃvāso”ti.* **";
P_HTM[12092]="*Dutiyampi kho so puggalo tuṇhī ahosi.* **";
P_HTM[12093]="*Tatiyampi kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno taṃ puggalaṃ etadavoca—**and a third time,*";
P_HTM[12094]="*“uṭṭhehi, āvuso, diṭṭhosi bhagavatā;* **";
P_HTM[12095]="*natthi te bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ saṃvāso”ti.* **";
P_HTM[12096]="*Tatiyampi kho so puggalo tuṇhī ahosi.**still not getting a reply.*";
P_HTM[12097]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno taṃ puggalaṃ bāhāyaṃ gahetvā bahidvārakoṭṭhakā nikkhāmetvā sūcighaṭikaṃ datvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**Mahāmoggallāna then grabbed him by the arms, took him outside the gateway, and fastened the bolts. And he went to the Buddha and said,*";
P_HTM[12098]="*“nikkhāmito so, bhante, puggalo mayā;**“Sir, I have taken that person outside;*";
P_HTM[12099]="*suddhā parisā;**the gathering is pure.*";
P_HTM[12100]="*uddisatu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhūnaṃ pātimokkhan”ti.**Please recite the Monastic Code to the monks.”*";
P_HTM[12101]="*“Acchariyaṃ, moggallāna, abbhutaṃ, moggallāna, yāva bāhāgahaṇāpi nāma so moghapuriso āgamessatī”ti.**“It’s amazing, Moggallāna, how that fool waited until he was grabbed by the arms.”*";
P_HTM[12102]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi—**And the Buddha addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[12103]="*2. Mahāsamuddeaṭṭhacchariya**2. The eight amazing qualities of the ocean*";
P_HTM[12104]="*“Aṭṭhime, bhikkhave, mahāsamudde acchariyā abbhutā dhammā, ye disvā disvā asurā mahāsamudde abhiramanti.**“Monks, the antigods delight in the ocean when they see these eight amazing qualities in it:*";
P_HTM[12105]="*Katame aṭṭha?* **";
P_HTM[12106]="*Mahāsamuddo, bhikkhave, anupubbaninno anupubbapoṇo anupubbapabbhāro na āyatakeneva papāto.**The ocean slopes and inclines gradually. It does not drop off all at once.*";
P_HTM[12107]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, mahāsamuddo anupubbaninno anupubbapoṇo anupubbapabbhāro na āyatakeneva papāto—* **";
P_HTM[12108]="*ayaṃ, bhikkhave, mahāsamudde paṭhamo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ disvā disvā asurā mahāsamudde abhiramanti.* **";
P_HTM[12109]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, mahāsamuddo ṭhitadhammo velaṃ nātivattati.**The ocean is steady. It does not go beyond the shoreline.*";
P_HTM[12110]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, mahāsamuddo ṭhitadhammo velaṃ nātivattati—* **";
P_HTM[12111]="*ayaṃ, bhikkhave, mahāsamudde dutiyo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ disvā disvā asurā mahāsamudde abhiramanti.* **";
P_HTM[12112]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, mahāsamuddo na matena kuṇapena saṃvasati. Yaṃ hoti mahāsamudde mataṃ kuṇapaṃ, taṃ khippaññeva tīraṃ vāheti, thalaṃ ussāreti.**The ocean does not tolerate dead bodies, but quickly carries them to the shore and discards them on dry land.*";
P_HTM[12113]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, mahāsamuddo na matena kuṇapena saṃvasati, yaṃ hoti mahāsamudde mataṃ kuṇapaṃ, taṃ khippaññeva tīraṃ vāheti, thalaṃ ussāreti—* **";
P_HTM[12114]="*ayaṃ, bhikkhave, mahāsamudde tatiyo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ disvā disvā asurā mahāsamudde abhiramanti.* **";
P_HTM[12115]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, yā kāci mahānadiyo, seyyathidaṃ—gaṅgā, yamunā, aciravatī, sarabhū, mahī, tā mahāsamuddaṃ pattā jahanti purimāni nāmagottāni, mahāsamuddotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchanti.**When the great rivers—the Ganges, the Yamunā, the Aciravatī, the Sarabhū, or the Mahī—reach the ocean, they lose their former names and become known simply as the ocean.*";
P_HTM[12116]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, yā kāci mahānadiyo, seyyathidaṃ—gaṅgā, yamunā, aciravatī, sarabhū, mahī, tā mahāsamuddaṃ pattā jahanti purimāni nāmagottāni, mahāsamuddotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchanti—* **";
P_HTM[12117]="*ayaṃ, bhikkhave, mahāsamudde catuttho acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ disvā disvā asurā mahāsamudde abhiramanti.* **";
P_HTM[12118]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, yā ca loke savantiyo mahāsamuddaṃ appenti, yā ca antalikkhā dhārā papatanti, na tena mahāsamuddassa ūnattaṃ vā pūrattaṃ vā paññāyati.**Whatever rivers in the world flow into the ocean and whatever rain falls into it, the ocean is not diminished or filled up because of that.*";
P_HTM[12119]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, yā ca loke savantiyo mahāsamuddaṃ appenti, yā ca antalikkhā dhārā papatanti, na tena mahāsamuddassa ūnattaṃ vā pūrattaṃ vā paññāyati—* **";
P_HTM[12120]="*ayaṃ, bhikkhave, mahāsamudde pañcamo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ disvā disvā asurā mahāsamudde abhiramanti.* **";
P_HTM[12121]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, mahāsamuddo ekaraso loṇaraso.**The ocean has only one taste, the taste of salt.*";
P_HTM[12122]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, mahāsamuddo ekaraso loṇaraso—* **";
P_HTM[12123]="*ayaṃ, bhikkhave, mahāsamudde chaṭṭho acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ disvā disvā asurā mahāsamudde abhiramanti.* **";
P_HTM[12124]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, mahāsamuddo bahuratano anekaratano. Tatrimāni ratanāni, seyyathidaṃ—muttā, maṇi, veḷuriyo, saṅkho, silā, pavāḷaṃ, rajataṃ, jātarūpaṃ, lohitako, masāragallaṃ.**The ocean contains many precious things—pearls, gems, beryls, mother-of-pearls, quartz, corals, silver, gold, rubies, and cat’s eyes.*";
P_HTM[12125]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, mahāsamuddo bahuratano anekaratano, tatrimāni ratanāni, seyyathidaṃ—muttā, maṇi, veḷuriyo, saṅkho, silā, pavāḷaṃ, rajataṃ, jātarūpaṃ, lohitako, masāragallaṃ—* **";
P_HTM[12126]="*ayaṃ, bhikkhave, mahāsamudde sattamo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ disvā disvā asurā mahāsamudde abhiramanti.* **";
P_HTM[12127]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, mahāsamuddo mahataṃ bhūtānaṃ āvāso. Tatrime bhūtā—timi, timiṅgalo, timitimiṅgalo, asurā, nāgā, gandhabbā. Santi mahāsamudde yojanasatikāpi attabhāvā, dviyojanasatikāpi attabhāvā, tiyojanasatikāpi attabhāvā, catuyojanasatikāpi attabhāvā, pañcayojanasatikāpi attabhāvā.**There are great beings in the ocean—sea-monsters, antigods, dragons, and divinities; creatures with bodies one thousand kilometers long, two thousand, three thousand, four thousand, and five thousand kilometers long.*";
P_HTM[12128]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, mahāsamuddo mahataṃ bhūtānaṃ āvāso, tatrime bhūtā—timi, timiṅgalo, timitimiṅgalo, asurā, nāgā, gandhabbā; santi mahāsamudde, yojanasatikāpi attabhāvā …pe… pañcayojanasatikāpi attabhāvā—* **";
P_HTM[12129]="*ayaṃ, bhikkhave, mahāsamudde aṭṭhamo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ disvā disvā asurā mahāsamudde abhiramanti.* **";
P_HTM[12130]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, mahāsamudde aṭṭha acchariyā abbhutā dhammā, ye disvā disvā asurā mahāsamudde abhiraman”ti.* **";
P_HTM[12131]="*3. Imasmiṃdhammavinayeaṭṭhacchariya**3. The eight amazing qualities of this spiritual path*";
P_HTM[12132]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye aṭṭha acchariyā abbhutā dhammā, ye disvā disvā bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye abhiramanti.**“Just so, the monks delight in this spiritual path when they see these eight amazing qualities in it:*";
P_HTM[12133]="*Katame aṭṭha?* **";
P_HTM[12134]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, mahāsamuddo anupubbaninno anupubbapoṇo anupubbapabbhāro na āyatakeneva papāto;**Just as the ocean slopes and inclines gradually, and does not drop off all at once,*";
P_HTM[12135]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye anupubbasikkhā anupubbakiriyā anupubbapaṭipadā na āyatakeneva aññāpaṭivedho.**so too, on this spiritual path, the training is gradual, the practice is gradual, and penetration to perfect insight does not happen all at once.*";
P_HTM[12136]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye anupubbasikkhā anupubbakiriyā anupubbapaṭipadā na āyatakeneva aññāpaṭivedho—* **";
P_HTM[12137]="*ayaṃ, bhikkhave, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye paṭhamo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ disvā disvā bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye abhiramanti.* **";
P_HTM[12138]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, mahāsamuddo ṭhitadhammo velaṃ nātivattati;**Just as the ocean is steady and does not go beyond the shoreline,*";
P_HTM[12139]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, yaṃ mayā mama sāvakānaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ, taṃ mama sāvakā jīvitahetupi nātikkamanti.**so too, on this spiritual path, my disciples don’t transgress the training rules I have laid down, even for the sake of life.*";
P_HTM[12140]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, mayā mama sāvakānaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ, taṃ mama sāvakā jīvitahetupi nātikkamanti—* **";
P_HTM[12141]="*ayaṃ, bhikkhave, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye dutiyo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ disvā disvā bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye abhiramanti.* **";
P_HTM[12142]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, mahāsamuddo na matena kuṇapena saṃvasati, yaṃ hoti mahāsamudde mataṃ kuṇapaṃ taṃ khippameva tīraṃ vāheti, thalaṃ ussāreti;**Just as the ocean does not tolerate dead bodies, but quickly carries them to the shore and discards them on dry land,*";
P_HTM[12143]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, yo so puggalo dussīlo pāpadhammo asucisaṅkassarasamācāro paṭicchannakammanto assamaṇo samaṇapaṭiñño abrahmacārī brahmacāripaṭiñño antopūti avassuto kasambujāto, na tena saṅgho saṃvasati, khippameva naṃ sannipatitvā ukkhipati, kiñcāpi kho so hoti majjhe bhikkhusaṅghassa nisinno. Atha kho so ārakāva saṅghamhā, saṅgho ca tena.**so too, the Sangha of monks does not associate with anyone who is immoral—someone with bad qualities, impure and dubious in conduct, hiding his actions, not a monastic while claiming to be one, not abstaining from sexuality while claiming to do so, rotten inside, lustful, defiled. When the Sangha has gathered , they quickly eject him. Even if he is seated in the midst of the Sangha, he is far from the Sangha and the Sangha is far from him.*";
P_HTM[12144]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, yo so puggalo dussīlo pāpadhammo asucisaṅkassarasamācāro paṭicchannakammanto assamaṇo samaṇapaṭiñño abrahmacārī brahmacāripaṭiñño antopūti avassuto kasambujāto, na tena saṅgho saṃvasati, khippameva naṃ sannipatitvā ukkhipati, kiñcāpi kho so hoti majjhe bhikkhusaṅghassa nisinno, atha kho so ārakāva saṅghamhā, saṅgho ca tena—* **";
P_HTM[12145]="*ayaṃ, bhikkhave, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye tatiyo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ disvā disvā bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye abhiramanti.* **";
P_HTM[12146]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yā kāci mahānadiyo, seyyathidaṃ—gaṅgā, yamunā, aciravatī, sarabhū, mahī, tā mahāsamuddaṃ pattā jahanti purimāni nāmagottāni, mahāsamuddotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchanti;**Just as when the great rivers—the Ganges, the Yamunā, the Aciravatī, the Sarabhū, or the Mahī—reach the ocean, they lose their former names and become known simply as the ocean,*";
P_HTM[12147]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, cattārome vaṇṇā—khattiyā, brāhmaṇā, vessā, suddā. Te tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitvā jahanti purimāni nāmagottāni, samaṇā sakyaputtiyātveva saṅkhaṃ gacchanti.**so too, when anyone who goes forth on this spiritual path made known by the Buddha—whether aristocrats, brahmins, merchants, or workers—they lose their former name and class and become known simply as Sakyans monastics.*";
P_HTM[12148]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, cattārome vaṇṇā khattiyā brāhmaṇā vessā suddā, te tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitvā jahanti purimāni nāmagottāni, samaṇā sakyaputtiyātveva saṅkhaṃ gacchanti—* **";
P_HTM[12149]="*ayaṃ, bhikkhave, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye catuttho acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ disvā disvā bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye abhiramanti.* **";
P_HTM[12150]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yā ca loke savantiyo mahāsamuddaṃ appenti, yā ca antalikkhā dhārā papatanti, na tena mahāsamuddassa ūnattaṃ vā pūrattaṃ vā paññāyati;**Just as the ocean does not decrease or fill up because of all the rivers in the world that flow into it or the rain that falls into it,*";
P_HTM[12151]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, bahū cepi bhikkhū anupādisesāya nibbānadhātuyā parinibbāyanti, na tena nibbānadhātuyā ūnattaṃ vā pūrattaṃ vā paññāyati.**so too, even if many monks are extinguished without remainder, there is no decrease or filling up of the element of extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[12152]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, bahū cepi bhikkhū anupādisesāya nibbānadhātuyā parinibbāyanti, na tena nibbānadhātuyā ūnattaṃ vā pūrattaṃ vā paññāyati—* **";
P_HTM[12153]="*ayaṃ, bhikkhave, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye pañcamo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo yaṃ disvā disvā bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye abhiramanti.* **";
P_HTM[12154]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, mahāsamuddo ekaraso loṇaraso;**Just as the ocean has only one taste, the taste of salt,*";
P_HTM[12155]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, ayaṃ dhammavinayo ekaraso vimuttiraso.**so too, this spiritual path has only one taste, the taste of freedom.*";
P_HTM[12156]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, ayaṃ dhammavinayo ekaraso vimuttiraso—* **";
P_HTM[12157]="*ayaṃ, bhikkhave, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye chaṭṭho acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ disvā disvā bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye abhiramanti.* **";
P_HTM[12158]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, mahāsamuddo bahuratano anekaratano, tatrimāni ratanāni, seyyathidaṃ—muttā, maṇi, veḷuriyo, saṅkho, silā, pavāḷaṃ, rajataṃ, jātarūpaṃ, lohitako, masāragallaṃ;**Just as the ocean contains many precious things—pearls, gems, beryls, mother-of-pearls, quartz, corals, silver, gold, rubies, and cat’s eyes—*";
P_HTM[12159]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, ayaṃ dhammavinayo bahuratano anekaratano. Tatrimāni ratanāni, seyyathidaṃ—cattāro satipaṭṭhānā, cattāro sammappadhānā, cattāro iddhipādā, pañcindriyāni, pañca balāni, satta bojjhaṅgā, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo.**so too, this spiritual path contains many precious things—the four applications of mindfulness, the four right efforts, the four foundations for supernormal power, the five spiritual faculties, the five spiritual powers, the seven factors of awakening, and the noble eightfold path.*";
P_HTM[12160]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, ayaṃ dhammavinayo bahuratano anekaratano, tatrimāni ratanāni, seyyathidaṃ—cattāro satipaṭṭhānā …pe… ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo—* **";
P_HTM[12161]="*ayaṃ, bhikkhave, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye sattamo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ disvā disvā bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye abhiramanti.* **";
P_HTM[12162]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, mahāsamuddo mahataṃ bhūtānaṃ āvāso, tatrime bhūtā—timi, timiṅgalo, timitimiṅgalo, asurā, nāgā, gandhabbā, santi mahāsamudde yojanasatikāpi attabhāvā, dviyojanasatikāpi attabhāvā, tiyojanasatikāpi attabhāvā, catuyojanasatikāpi attabhāvā, pañcayojanasatikāpi attabhāvā;**Just as there are great beings in the ocean—sea-monsters, antigods, dragons, and divinities; creatures with bodies one thousand kilometers long, two thousand, three thousand, four thousand, and five thousand kilometers long—*";
P_HTM[12163]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, ayaṃ dhammavinayo mahataṃ bhūtānaṃ āvāso. Tatrime bhūtā—sotāpanno, sotāpattiphalasacchikiriyāya paṭipanno; sakadāgāmī, sakadāgāmiphalasacchikiriyāya paṭipanno; anāgāmī, anāgāmiphalasacchikiriyāya paṭipanno; arahā, arahattaphalasacchikiriyāya paṭipanno.**so too, there are great beings on this spiritual path—stream-enterers, those practicing for the realization of the fruit of stream-entry; once-returners, those practicing for the realization of the fruit of once-returning; non-returners, those practicing for the realization of the fruit of non-returning; perfected ones, and those practicing for the realization of the fruit of perfection.”*";
P_HTM[12164]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, ayaṃ dhammavinayo mahataṃ bhūtānaṃ āvāso, tatrime bhūtā—sotāpanno, sotāpattiphalasacchikiriyāya paṭipanno …pe… arahā, arahattaphalasacchikiriyāya paṭipanno—* **";
P_HTM[12165]="*ayaṃ, bhikkhave, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye aṭṭhamo acchariyo abbhuto dhammo, yaṃ disvā disvā bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye abhiramanti.* **";
P_HTM[12166]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye aṭṭha acchariyā abbhutā dhammā, ye disvā disvā bhikkhū imasmiṃ dhammavinaye abhiramantī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[12167]="*Atha kho bhagavā etamatthaṃ viditvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ udānaṃ udānesi—**Seeing the significance of this, on that occasion the Buddha uttered a heartfelt exclamation:*";
P_HTM[12168]="*“Channamativassati,**“It rains on what’s concealed,*";
P_HTM[12169]="*vivaṭaṃ nātivassati;**Not on what’s revealed.*";
P_HTM[12170]="*Tasmā channaṃ vivaretha,**Therefore, reveal the concealed,*";
P_HTM[12171]="*evaṃ taṃ nātivassatī”ti.**And it will not be rained upon.”*";
P_HTM[12172]="*4. Pātimokkhasavanāraha**4. One deserving to hear the Monastic Code*";
P_HTM[12173]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi—**And the Buddha addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[12174]="*“nadānāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ito paraṃ uposathaṃ karissāmi, pātimokkhaṃ uddisissāmi.**“From now on I won’t do the observance-day procedure or recite the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[12175]="*Tumhevadāni, bhikkhave, ito paraṃ uposathaṃ kareyyātha, pātimokkhaṃ uddiseyyātha.**You will be doing it instead.*";
P_HTM[12176]="*Aṭṭhānametaṃ, bhikkhave, anavakāso yaṃ tathāgato aparisuddhāya parisāya uposathaṃ kareyya, pātimokkhaṃ uddiseyya.**It’s impossible for the Buddha to do the observance-day procedure and recite the Monastic Code in an impure gathering.*";
P_HTM[12177]="*Na ca, bhikkhave, sāpattikena pātimokkhaṃ sotabbaṃ.**And, monks, you should not listen to the Monastic Code if you have an unconfessed offense.*";
P_HTM[12178]="*Yo suṇeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12179]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, yo sāpattiko pātimokkhaṃ suṇāti, tassa pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapetuṃ.**If anyone who has an unconfessed offense listens to the Monastic Code, I allow you to cancel his hearing of the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[12180]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, ṭhapetabbaṃ.**And it’s to be done like this.*";
P_HTM[12181]="*Tadahuposathe cātuddase vā pannarase vā tasmiṃ puggale sammukhībhūte saṅghamajjhe udāharitabbaṃ—**On the observance day, whether the fourteenth or the fifteenth, in the midst of the Sangha and in the presence of that person, you should announce:*";
P_HTM[12182]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[12183]="*Itthannāmo puggalo sāpattiko, tassa pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapemi, na tasmiṃ sammukhībhūte pātimokkhaṃ uddisitabban’ti ṭhapitaṃ hoti pātimokkhan”ti.**The person so-and-so has an unconfessed offense. I cancel his hearing of the Monastic Code. The Monastic Code should not be recited in his presence.’ Then the Monastic Code is canceled for him.”*";
P_HTM[12184]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū—**Soon afterwards,*";
P_HTM[12185]="*“nāmhe koci jānātī”ti sāpattikāva pātimokkhaṃ suṇanti.**thinking that nobody knew about them, the monks from the group of six listened to the Monastic Code while having unconfessed offenses.*";
P_HTM[12186]="*Therā bhikkhū paracittaviduno bhikkhūnaṃ ārocenti—**The senior monks who could read the minds of others*";
P_HTM[12187]="*“itthannāmo ca itthannāmo ca, āvuso, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū—**informed the monks about this.*";
P_HTM[12188]="*‘nāmhe koci jānātī’ti sāpattikāva pātimokkhaṃ suṇantī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[12189]="*Assosuṃ kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū—**When they heard about this,*";
P_HTM[12190]="*“therā kira bhikkhū paracittaviduno amhe bhikkhūnaṃ ārocenti—* **";
P_HTM[12191]="*‘itthannāmo ca itthannāmo ca, āvuso, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū—* **";
P_HTM[12192]="*“nāmhe koci jānātī”ti sāpattikāva pātimokkhaṃ suṇantī’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[12193]="*Te—* **";
P_HTM[12194]="*“puramhākaṃ pesalā bhikkhū pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapentī”ti—* **";
P_HTM[12195]="*paṭikacceva suddhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ anāpattikānaṃ avatthusmiṃ akāraṇe pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapenti.**the monks from the group of six canceled, without reason, the Monastic Code of the pure monks to preempt them.*";
P_HTM[12196]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12197]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū suddhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ anāpattikānaṃ avatthusmiṃ akāraṇe pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapessantī”ti.**“How can the monks from the group of six cancel the Monastic Code of pure monks without reason?”*";
P_HTM[12198]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[12199]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū suddhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ anāpattikānaṃ avatthusmiṃ akāraṇe pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the monks from the group of six did this?”*";
P_HTM[12200]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti …pe…**“It’s true, Sir.” …*";
P_HTM[12201]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[12202]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[12203]="*“na, bhikkhave, suddhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ anāpattikānaṃ avatthusmiṃ akāraṇe pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapetabbaṃ.**“You should not, without reason, cancel the Monastic Code of pure monks who don’t have any offenses.*";
P_HTM[12204]="*Yo ṭhapeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12205]="*5. Dhammikādhammikapātimokkhaṭṭhapana**5. Legitimate and illegitimate canceling of the Monastic Code*";
P_HTM[12206]="*Ekaṃ, bhikkhave, adhammikaṃ pātimokkhaṭṭhapanaṃ, ekaṃ dhammikaṃ pātimokkhaṭṭhapanaṃ;**“One kind of canceling of the Monastic Code is illegitimate, one is legitimate;*";
P_HTM[12207]="*dve adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni, dve dhammikāni;**two kinds of cancelings of the Monastic Code are illegitimate, two are legitimate;*";
P_HTM[12208]="*tīṇi adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni, tīṇi dhammikāni;**three kinds of cancelings of the Monastic Code are illegitimate, three are legitimate;*";
P_HTM[12209]="*cattāri adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni, cattāri dhammikāni;**four kinds of cancelings of the Monastic Code are illegitimate, four are legitimate;*";
P_HTM[12210]="*pañca adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni, pañca dhammikāni;**five kinds of cancelings of the Monastic Code are illegitimate, five are legitimate;*";
P_HTM[12211]="*cha adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni, cha dhammikāni;**six kinds of cancelings of the Monastic Code are illegitimate, six are legitimate;*";
P_HTM[12212]="*satta adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni, satta dhammikāni;**seven kinds of cancelings of the Monastic Code are illegitimate, seven are legitimate;*";
P_HTM[12213]="*aṭṭha adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni, aṭṭha dhammikāni;**eight kinds of cancelings of the Monastic Code are illegitimate, eight are legitimate;*";
P_HTM[12214]="*nava adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni, nava dhammikāni;**nine kinds of cancelings of the Monastic Code are illegitimate, nine are legitimate;*";
P_HTM[12215]="*dasa adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni, dasa dhammikāni.**ten kinds of cancelings of the Monastic Code are illegitimate, ten are legitimate.*";
P_HTM[12216]="*Katamaṃ ekaṃ adhammikaṃ pātimokkhaṭṭhapanaṃ?**“What is the one kind of canceling of the Monastic Code that is illegitimate?*";
P_HTM[12217]="*Amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti—**One cancels the Monastic Code, without grounds, for failure in morality.*";
P_HTM[12218]="*idaṃ ekaṃ adhammikaṃ pātimokkhaṭṭhapanaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[12219]="*Katamaṃ ekaṃ dhammikaṃ pātimokkhaṭṭhapanaṃ?**What is the one kind of canceling of the Monastic Code that is legitimate?*";
P_HTM[12220]="*Samūlikāya sīlavipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti—**One cancels the Monastic Code, having grounds, for failure in morality.*";
P_HTM[12221]="*idaṃ ekaṃ dhammikaṃ pātimokkhaṭṭhapanaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[12222]="*Katamāni dve adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni?**“What are the two kinds of cancelings of the Monastic Code that are illegitimate?*";
P_HTM[12223]="*Amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti, amūlikāya ācāravipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti—**One cancels the Monastic Code, without grounds, for failure in morality or for failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[12224]="*imāni dve adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.* **";
P_HTM[12225]="*Katamāni dve dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni?**What are the two kinds of cancelings of the Monastic Code that are legitimate?*";
P_HTM[12226]="*Samūlikāya sīlavipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti, samūlikāya ācāravipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti—**One cancels the Monastic Code, having grounds, for failure in morality or for failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[12227]="*imāni dve dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.* **";
P_HTM[12228]="*Katamāni tīṇi adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni?**“What are the three kinds of cancelings of the Monastic Code that are illegitimate?*";
P_HTM[12229]="*Amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti, amūlikāya ācāravipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti, amūlikāya diṭṭhivipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti—**One cancels the Monastic Code, without grounds, for failure in morality, for failure in conduct, or for failure in view.*";
P_HTM[12230]="*imāni tīṇi adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.* **";
P_HTM[12231]="*Katamāni tīṇi dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni?**What are the three kinds of cancelings of the Monastic Code that are legitimate?*";
P_HTM[12232]="*Samūlikāya sīlavipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti, samūlikāya ācāravipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti, samūlikāya diṭṭhivipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti—**One cancels the Monastic Code, having grounds, for failure in morality, for failure in conduct, or for failure in view.*";
P_HTM[12233]="*imāni tīṇi dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.* **";
P_HTM[12234]="*Katamāni cattāri adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni?**“What are the four kinds of cancelings of the Monastic Code that are illegitimate?*";
P_HTM[12235]="*Amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti, amūlikāya ācāravipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti, amūlikāya diṭṭhivipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti, amūlikāya ājīvavipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti—**One cancels the Monastic Code, without grounds, for failure in morality, for failure in conduct, for failure in view, or for failure in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[12236]="*imāni cattāri adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.* **";
P_HTM[12237]="*Katamāni cattāri dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni?**What are the four kinds of cancelings of the Monastic Code that are legitimate?*";
P_HTM[12238]="*Samūlikāya sīlavipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti, samūlikāya ācāravipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti, samūlikāya diṭṭhivipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti, samūlikāya ājīvavipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti—**One cancels the Monastic Code, having grounds, for failure in morality, for failure in conduct, for failure in view, or for failure in livelihood.*";
P_HTM[12239]="*imāni cattāri dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.* **";
P_HTM[12240]="*Katamāni pañca adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni?**“What are the five kinds of cancelings of the Monastic Code that are illegitimate?*";
P_HTM[12241]="*Amūlakena pārājikena pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti, amūlakena saṅghādisesena …pe…**One cancels the Monastic Code, groundlessly, for an offense entailing expulsion, for an offense entailing suspension,*";
P_HTM[12242]="*amūlakena pācittiyena …**for an offense entailing confession,*";
P_HTM[12243]="*amūlakena pāṭidesanīyena …**for an offense entailing acknowledgment,*";
P_HTM[12244]="*amūlakena dukkaṭena pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti—**or for an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12245]="*imāni pañca adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.* **";
P_HTM[12246]="*Katamāni pañca dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni?**What are the five kinds of cancelings of the Monastic Code that are legitimate?*";
P_HTM[12247]="*Samūlakena pārājikena pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti, samūlakena saṅghādisesena …pe…**One cancels the Monastic Code, having grounds, for an offense entailing expulsion, for an offense entailing suspension,*";
P_HTM[12248]="*pācittiyena …**for an offense entailing confession,*";
P_HTM[12249]="*pāṭidesanīyena …**for an offense entailing acknowledgment,*";
P_HTM[12250]="*dukkaṭena pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti—**or for an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12251]="*imāni pañca dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.* **";
P_HTM[12252]="*Katamāni cha adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni?**“What are the six kinds of cancelings of the Monastic Code that are illegitimate?*";
P_HTM[12253]="*Amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti akatāya, amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti katāya;**One cancels the Monastic Code, without grounds, for the failure in morality of one who hasn’t failed, for the failure in morality of one who has failed,*";
P_HTM[12254]="*amūlikāya ācāravipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti akatāya, amūlikāya ācāravipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti katāya;**for the failure in conduct of one who hasn’t failed, for the failure in conduct of one who has failed,*";
P_HTM[12255]="*amūlikāya diṭṭhivipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti akatāya, amūlikāya diṭṭhivipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti katāya—**for the failure in view of one who hasn’t failed, or for the failure in view of one who has failed.*";
