P_HTM[12281]="*ājīvavipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti akatāya …pe… katāya—**for the failure in livelihood of one who hasn’t failed, for the failure in livelihood of one who has failed.*";
P_HTM[12282]="*imāni aṭṭha dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.* **";
P_HTM[12283]="*Katamāni nava adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni?**“What are the nine kinds of cancelings of the Monastic Code that are illegitimate?*";
P_HTM[12284]="*Amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti akatāya, amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti katāya, amūlikāya sīlavipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti katākatāya;**One cancels the Monastic Code, without grounds, for the failure in morality of one who hasn’t failed, for the failure in morality of one who has failed, for the failure in morality of one who both has and hasn’t failed,*";
P_HTM[12285]="*amūlikāya ācāravipattiyā …pe…**for the failure in conduct of one who hasn’t failed, for the failure in conduct of one who has failed, for the failure in conduct of one who both has and hasn’t failed,*";
P_HTM[12286]="*diṭṭhivipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti akatāya …pe… katāya …pe…**for the failure in view of one who hasn’t failed, for the failure in view of one who has failed, for the failure in view of one who both has and hasn’t failed.*";
P_HTM[12287]="*katākatāya—* **";
P_HTM[12288]="*imāni nava adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.* **";
P_HTM[12289]="*Katamāni nava dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni?**What are the nine kinds of cancelings of the Monastic Code that are legitimate?*";
P_HTM[12290]="*Samūlikāya sīlavipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti akatāya, samūlikāya sīlavipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti katāya, samūlikāya sīlavipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti katākatāya;**One cancels the Monastic Code, having grounds, for the failure in morality of one who hasn’t failed, for the failure in morality of one who has failed, for the failure in morality of one who both has and hasn’t failed,*";
P_HTM[12291]="*samūlikāya ācāravipattiyā …pe…**for the failure in conduct of one who hasn’t failed, for the failure in conduct of one who has failed, for the failure in conduct of one who both has and hasn’t failed,*";
P_HTM[12292]="*diṭṭhivipattiyā pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti akatāya …pe… katāya …pe…**for the failure in view of one who hasn’t failed, for the failure in view of one who has failed, for the failure in view of one who both has and hasn’t failed.*";
P_HTM[12293]="*katākatāya—* **";
P_HTM[12294]="*imāni nava dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.* **";
P_HTM[12295]="*Katamāni dasa adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni?**“What are the ten kinds of cancelings of the Monastic Code that are illegitimate?*";
P_HTM[12296]="*Na pārājiko tassaṃ parisāyaṃ nisinno hoti, na pārājikakathā vippakatā hoti;**There is no one seated in that gathering who has committed an offense entailing expulsion; there is no unfinished discussion on anyone committing an offense entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[12297]="*na sikkhaṃ paccakkhātako tassaṃ parisāyaṃ nisinno hoti, na sikkhaṃ paccakkhātakathā vippakatā hoti;**no one seated in that gathering has renounced the training; there is no unfinished discussion on anyone renouncing the training;*";
P_HTM[12298]="*dhammikaṃ sāmaggiṃ upeti, na dhammikaṃ sāmaggiṃ paccādiyati, na dhammikāya sāmaggiyā paccādānakathā vippakatā hoti;**he goes to the legitimate legal procedure of a complete assembly; he doesn’t reopen a legitimate legal procedure of a complete assembly; there is no unfinished discussion on the reopening of a legitimate legal procedure of a complete assembly;*";
P_HTM[12299]="*na sīlavipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkito hoti, na ācāravipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkito hoti, na diṭṭhivipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkito hoti—**no one has seen, heard, or suspects any failure in morality; no one has seen, heard, or suspects any failure in conduct; no one has seen, heard, or suspects any failure in view.*";
P_HTM[12300]="*imāni dasa adhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.* **";
P_HTM[12301]="*Katamāni dasa dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni?**What are the ten kinds of cancelings of the Monastic Code that are legitimate?*";
P_HTM[12302]="*Pārājiko tassaṃ parisāyaṃ nisinno hoti, pārājikakathā vippakatā hoti;**There is someone seated in that gathering who has committed an offense entailing expulsion; there is an unfinished discussion on someone committing an offense entailing expulsion;*";
P_HTM[12303]="*sikkhaṃ paccakkhātako tassaṃ parisāyaṃ nisinno hoti, sikkhaṃ paccakkhātakathā vippakatā hoti;**someone seated in that gathering has renounced the training; there is an unfinished discussion on someone renouncing the training;*";
P_HTM[12304]="*dhammikaṃ sāmaggiṃ na upeti, dhammikaṃ sāmaggiṃ paccādiyati, dhammikāya sāmaggiyā paccādānakathā vippakatā hoti;**he doesn’t go to a legitimate legal procedure of a complete assembly; he reopens a legitimate legal procedure of a complete assembly; there is an unfinished discussion on the reopening of a legitimate legal procedure of a complete assembly;*";
P_HTM[12305]="*sīlavipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkito hoti, ācāravipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkito hoti, diṭṭhivipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkito hoti—**someone has seen, heard, or suspects failure in morality; someone has seen, heard, or suspects failure in conduct; someone has seen, heard, or suspects failure in view.*";
P_HTM[12306]="*imāni dasa dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanāni.* **";
P_HTM[12307]="*6. Dhammikapātimokkhaṭṭhapana**6. Legitimate canceling of the Monastic Code*";
P_HTM[12308]="*Kathaṃ pārājiko tassaṃ parisāyaṃ nisinno hoti?**“And how is one who has committed an offense entailing expulsion seated in that gathering?*";
P_HTM[12309]="*Idha, bhikkhave, yehi ākārehi yehi liṅgehi yehi nimittehi pārājikassa dhammassa ajjhāpatti hoti, tehi ākārehi tehi liṅgehi tehi nimittehi bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ passati pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ ajjhāpajjantaṃ.**A monk sees in a monk the characteristics and signs of someone committing an offense entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[12310]="*Na heva kho bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ passati pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ ajjhāpajjantaṃ, api ca añño bhikkhu bhikkhussa āroceti—**Or a monk doesn’t see a monk committing an offense entailing expulsion, but another monk informs him,*";
P_HTM[12311]="*‘itthannāmo, āvuso, bhikkhu pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ ajjhāpanno’ti.**‘The monk so-and-so has committed an offense entailing expulsion.’*";
P_HTM[12312]="*Na heva kho bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ passati pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ ajjhāpajjantaṃ, nāpi añño bhikkhu bhikkhussa āroceti—**Or a monk doesn’t see a monk committing an offense entailing expulsion, nor does another monk inform him,*";
P_HTM[12313]="*‘itthannāmo, āvuso, bhikkhu pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ ajjhāpanno’ti, api ca sova bhikkhu bhikkhussa āroceti—**but the monk himself informs him,*";
P_HTM[12314]="*‘ahaṃ, āvuso, pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ ajjhāpanno’ti.**‘I have committed an offense entailing expulsion.’*";
P_HTM[12315]="*Ākaṅkhamāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tena diṭṭhena tena sutena tāya parisaṅkāya tadahuposathe cātuddase vā pannarase vā tasmiṃ puggale sammukhībhūte saṅghamajjhe udāhareyya—**Then, on the observance day, whether the fourteenth or the fifteenth, he may if he wishes, based on what he’s seen, heard, or suspects, announce in the midst of the Sangha and in the presence of that person:*";
P_HTM[12316]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[12317]="*Itthannāmo puggalo pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ ajjhāpanno, tassa pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapemi, na tasmiṃ sammukhībhūte pātimokkhaṃ uddisitabbanti—**So-and-so has committed an offense entailing expulsion. I cancel his hearing of the Monastic Code. The Monastic Code should not be recited in his presence.’*";
P_HTM[12318]="*dhammikaṃ pātimokkhaṭṭhapanaṃ’.**This cancellation of the Monastic Code is legitimate.*";
P_HTM[12319]="*Bhikkhussa pātimokkhe ṭhapite parisā vuṭṭhāti, dasannaṃ antarāyānaṃ aññatarena—**“When the Monastic Code has been canceled for a monk, it may be that the gathering breaks up because of any one of ten dangers:*";
P_HTM[12320]="*rājantarāyena vā, corantarāyena vā, agyantarāyena vā, udakantarāyena vā, manussantarāyena vā, amanussantarāyena vā, vāḷantarāyena vā, sarīsapantarāyena vā, jīvitantarāyena vā, brahmacariyantarāyena vā.**danger from kings, criminals, fire, flooding, people, spirits, predatory animals, snakes, or danger to life, or danger to living the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[12321]="*Ākaṅkhamāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tasmiṃ vā āvāse, aññasmiṃ vā āvāse, tasmiṃ puggale sammukhībhūte saṅghamajjhe udāhareyya—**Then, if a monk wishes, he may, in that monastery or in another monastery, announce in the midst of the Sangha and in the presence of that person:*";
P_HTM[12322]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[12323]="*Itthannāmassa puggalassa pārājikakathā vippakatā, taṃ vatthu avinicchitaṃ.**There is an unfinished discussion on so-and-so committing an offense entailing expulsion. The case has not been decided.*";
P_HTM[12324]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho taṃ vatthuṃ vinicchineyyā’ti.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should decide the case.’*";
P_HTM[12325]="*Evañcetaṃ labhetha, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ.**If this works out, all is well.*";
P_HTM[12326]="*No ce labhetha, tadahuposathe cātuddase vā pannarase vā tasmiṃ puggale sammukhībhūte saṅghamajjhe udāharitabbaṃ—**If not, then on the observance day, whether the fourteenth or the fifteenth, in the midst of the Sangha and in the presence of that person, a monk should announce:*";
P_HTM[12327]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[12328]="*Itthannāmassa puggalassa pārājikakathā vippakatā, taṃ vatthu avinicchitaṃ.**There is an unfinished discussion on so-and-so committing an offense entailing expulsion. The case has not been decided.*";
P_HTM[12329]="*Tassa pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapemi, na tasmiṃ sammukhībhūte pātimokkhaṃ uddisitabbanti—**I cancel his hearing of the Monastic Code. The Monastic Code should not be recited in his presence.’*";
P_HTM[12330]="*dhammikaṃ pātimokkhaṭṭhapanaṃ’.**This cancellation of the Monastic Code is legitimate.*";
P_HTM[12331]="*Kathaṃ sikkhaṃ paccakkhātako tassaṃ parisāyaṃ nisinno hoti?**“And how is one who has renounced the training seated in that gathering?*";
P_HTM[12332]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yehi ākārehi yehi liṅgehi yehi nimittehi sikkhā paccakkhātā hoti, tehi ākārehi tehi liṅgehi tehi nimittehi bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ passati sikkhaṃ paccakkhantaṃ.**A monk sees in a monk the characteristics and signs of someone renouncing the training.*";
P_HTM[12333]="*Na heva kho bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ passati sikkhaṃ paccakkhantaṃ, api ca añño bhikkhu bhikkhussa āroceti—**Or a monk doesn’t see a monk renouncing the training, but another monk informs him,*";
P_HTM[12334]="*‘itthannāmena, āvuso, bhikkhunā sikkhā paccakkhātā’ti.**‘The monk so-and-so has renounced the training.’*";
P_HTM[12335]="*Na heva kho bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ passati sikkhaṃ paccakkhantaṃ, nāpi añño bhikkhu bhikkhussa āroceti—**Or a monk doesn’t see a monk renouncing the training, nor does another monk inform him,*";
P_HTM[12336]="*‘itthannāmena, āvuso, bhikkhunā sikkhā paccakkhātā’ti, api ca sova bhikkhu bhikkhussa āroceti—**but the monk himself informs him,*";
P_HTM[12337]="*‘mayā, āvuso, sikkhā paccakkhātā’ti.**‘I have renounced the training.’*";
P_HTM[12338]="*Ākaṅkhamāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tena diṭṭhena tena sutena tāya parisaṅkāya tadahuposathe cātuddase vā pannarase vā tasmiṃ puggale sammukhībhūte saṅghamajjhe udāhareyya—**Then, on the observance day, whether the fourteenth or the fifteenth, he may if he wishes, based on what he’s seen, heard, or suspects, announce in the midst of the Sangha and in the presence of that person:*";
P_HTM[12339]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[12340]="*Itthannāmena puggalena sikkhā paccakkhātā, tassa pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapemi, na tasmiṃ sammukhībhūte pātimokkhaṃ uddisitabbanti—**So-and-so has renounced the training. I cancel his hearing of the Monastic Code. The Monastic Code should not be recited in his presence.’*";
P_HTM[12341]="*dhammikaṃ pātimokkhaṭṭhapanaṃ’.**This cancellation of the Monastic Code is legitimate.*";
P_HTM[12342]="*Bhikkhussa pātimokkhe ṭhapite parisā vuṭṭhāti, dasannaṃ antarāyānaṃ aññatarena—**“When the Monastic Code has been canceled for a monk, it may be that the gathering breaks up because of any one of ten dangers:*";
P_HTM[12343]="*rājantarāyena vā …pe…**danger from kings, criminals, fire, flooding, people, spirits, predatory animals, snakes, or danger to life,*";
P_HTM[12344]="*brahmacariyantarāyena vā, ākaṅkhamāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tasmiṃ vā āvāse, aññasmiṃ vā āvāse, tasmiṃ puggale sammukhībhūte saṅghamajjhe udāhareyya—**or danger to living the spiritual life. Then, if a monk wishes, he may, in that monastery or in another monastery, announce in the midst of the Sangha and in the presence of that person:*";
P_HTM[12345]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[12346]="*Itthannāmassa puggalassa sikkhaṃ paccakkhātakathā vippakatā, taṃ vatthu avinicchitaṃ.**There is an unfinished discussion on so-and-so renouncing the training. The case has not been decided.*";
P_HTM[12347]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho taṃ vatthuṃ vinicchineyyā’ti.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should decide the case.’*";
P_HTM[12348]="*Evañcetaṃ labhetha, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ.**If this works out, all is well.*";
P_HTM[12349]="*No ce labhetha, tadahuposathe cātuddase vā pannarase vā tasmiṃ puggale sammukhībhūte saṅghamajjhe udāharitabbaṃ—**If not, then on the observance day, whether the fourteenth or the fifteenth, in the midst of the Sangha and in the presence of that person, a monk should announce:*";
P_HTM[12350]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[12351]="*Itthannāmassa puggalassa sikkhaṃ paccakkhātakathā vippakatā, taṃ vatthu avinicchitaṃ.**There is an unfinished discussion on so-and-so renouncing the training. The matter has not been decided.*";
P_HTM[12352]="*Tassa pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapemi, na tasmiṃ sammukhībhūte pātimokkhaṃ uddisitabbanti—**I cancel his hearing of the Monastic Code. The Monastic Code should not be recited in his presence.’*";
P_HTM[12353]="*dhammikaṃ pātimokkhaṭṭhapanaṃ’.**This cancellation of the Monastic Code is legitimate.*";
P_HTM[12354]="*Kathaṃ dhammikaṃ sāmaggiṃ na upeti?**“And how does he not go to a legitimate legal procedure of a complete assembly?*";
P_HTM[12355]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yehi ākārehi yehi liṅgehi yehi nimittehi dhammikāya sāmaggiyānupagamanaṃ hoti, tehi ākārehi tehi liṅgehi tehi nimittehi bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ passati dhammikaṃ sāmaggiṃ na upentaṃ.**A monk sees in a monk the characteristics and signs of someone who doesn’t go to a legitimate legal procedure of a complete assembly.*";
P_HTM[12356]="*Na heva kho bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ passati dhammikaṃ sāmaggiṃ na upentaṃ, api ca añño bhikkhu bhikkhussa āroceti—**Or a monk doesn’t see a monk not going to a legitimate legal procedure of a complete assembly, but another monk informs him,*";
P_HTM[12357]="*‘itthannāmo, āvuso, bhikkhu dhammikaṃ sāmaggiṃ na upetī’ti.**‘Monk so-and-so didn’t go to a legitimate legal procedure of a complete assembly.’*";
P_HTM[12358]="*Na heva kho bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ passati dhammikaṃ sāmaggiṃ na upentaṃ, nāpi añño bhikkhu bhikkhussa āroceti—**Or a monk doesn’t see a monk not going to a legitimate legal procedure of a complete assembly, nor does another monk inform him,*";
P_HTM[12359]="*‘itthannāmo, āvuso, bhikkhu dhammikaṃ sāmaggiṃ na upetī’ti, api ca sova bhikkhu bhikkhussa āroceti—**but the monk himself informs him,*";
P_HTM[12360]="*‘ahaṃ, āvuso, dhammikaṃ sāmaggiṃ na upemī’ti.**‘I didn’t go to a legitimate legal procedure of a complete assembly.’*";
P_HTM[12361]="*Ākaṅkhamāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tena diṭṭhena tena sutena tāya parisaṅkāya tadahuposathe cātuddase vā pannarase vā tasmiṃ puggale sammukhībhūte saṅghamajjhe udāhareyya—**Then, on the observance day, whether the fourteenth or the fifteenth, he may if he wishes, based on what he’s seen, heard, or suspects, announce in the midst of the Sangha and in the presence of that person:*";
P_HTM[12362]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[12363]="*Itthannāmo puggalo dhammikaṃ sāmaggiṃ na upeti, tassa pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapemi, na tasmiṃ sammukhībhūte pātimokkhaṃ uddisitabbanti—**So-and-so did not go to a legitimate legal procedure of a complete assembly. I cancel his hearing of the Monastic Code. The Monastic Code should not be recited in his presence.’*";
P_HTM[12364]="*dhammikaṃ pātimokkhaṭṭhapanaṃ’.**This cancellation of the Monastic Code is legitimate.*";
P_HTM[12365]="*Kathaṃ dhammikaṃ sāmaggiṃ paccādiyati?**“And how does he reopen a legitimate legal procedure of a complete assembly?*";
P_HTM[12366]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yehi ākārehi yehi liṅgehi yehi nimittehi dhammikāya sāmaggiyā paccādānaṃ hoti, tehi ākārehi tehi liṅgehi tehi nimittehi bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ passati dhammikaṃ sāmaggiṃ paccādiyantaṃ.**A monk sees in a monk the characteristics and signs of someone who reopens a legitimate legal procedure of a complete assembly.*";
P_HTM[12367]="*Na heva kho bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ passati dhammikaṃ sāmaggiṃ paccādiyantaṃ, api ca añño bhikkhu bhikkhussa āroceti—‘itthannāmo, āvuso, bhikkhu dhammikaṃ sāmaggiṃ paccādiyatī’ti.**Or a monk doesn’t see a monk reopening a legitimate legal procedure of a complete assembly, but another monk informs him, ‘Monk so-and-so has reopened a legitimate legal procedure of a complete assembly.’*";
P_HTM[12368]="*Na heva kho bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ passati dhammikaṃ sāmaggiṃ paccādiyantaṃ, nāpi añño bhikkhu bhikkhussa āroceti—‘itthannāmo, āvuso, bhikkhu dhammikaṃ sāmaggiṃ paccādiyatī’ti, api ca sova bhikkhu bhikkhussa āroceti—‘ahaṃ, āvuso, dhammikaṃ sāmaggiṃ paccādiyāmī’ti.**Or a monk doesn’t see a monk reopening a legitimate legal procedure of a complete assembly, nor does another monk inform him, but the monk himself informs him, ‘I have reopened a legitimate legal procedure of a complete assembly.’*";
P_HTM[12369]="*Ākaṅkhamāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tena diṭṭhena tena sutena tāya parisaṅkāya tadahuposathe cātuddase vā pannarase vā tasmiṃ puggale sammukhībhūte saṅghamajjhe udāhareyya—**Then, on the observance day, whether the fourteenth or the fifteenth, he may if he wishes, based on what he’s seen, heard, or suspects, announce in the midst of the Sangha and in the presence of that person:*";
P_HTM[12370]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[12371]="*Itthannāmo puggalo dhammikaṃ sāmaggiṃ paccādiyati, tassa pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapemi, na tasmiṃ sammukhībhūte pātimokkhaṃ uddisitabbanti—**So-and-so has reopened a legitimate legal procedure of a complete assembly. I cancel his hearing of the Monastic Code. The Monastic Code should not be recited in his presence.’*";
P_HTM[12372]="*dhammikaṃ pātimokkhaṭṭhapanaṃ’.**This cancellation of the Monastic Code is legitimate.*";
P_HTM[12373]="*Bhikkhussa pātimokkhe ṭhapite parisā vuṭṭhāti, dasannaṃ antarāyānaṃ aññatarena—**“When the Monastic Code has been canceled for a monk, it may be that the gathering breaks up because of any one of ten dangers:*";
P_HTM[12374]="*rājantarāyena vā …pe…**danger from kings, criminals, fire, flooding, people, spirits, predatory animals, snakes, or danger to life,*";
P_HTM[12375]="*brahmacariyantarāyena vā.**or danger to living the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[12376]="*Ākaṅkhamāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tasmiṃ vā āvāse, aññasmiṃ vā āvāse, tasmiṃ puggale sammukhībhūte saṅghamajjhe udāhareyya—**Then, if a monk wishes, he may, in that monastery or in another monastery, announce in the midst of the Sangha and in the presence of that person:*";
P_HTM[12377]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[12378]="*Itthannāmassa puggalassa dhammikāya sāmaggiyā paccādānakathā vippakatā, taṃ vatthu avinicchitaṃ.**There is an unfinished discussion on so-and-so reopening a legitimate legal procedure of a complete assembly. The case has not been decided.*";
P_HTM[12379]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho taṃ vatthuṃ vinicchineyyā’ti.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should decide the case.’*";
P_HTM[12380]="*Evañcetaṃ labhetha, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ.**If this works out, all is well.*";
P_HTM[12381]="*No ce labhetha, tadahuposathe cātuddase vā pannarase vā tasmiṃ puggale sammukhībhūte saṅghamajjhe udāharitabbaṃ—**If not, then on the observance day, whether the fourteenth or the fifteenth, in the midst of the Sangha and in the presence of that person, a monk should announce:*";
P_HTM[12382]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[12383]="*Itthannāmassa puggalassa dhammikāya sāmaggiyā paccādānakathā vippakatā, taṃ vatthu avinicchitaṃ.**There is an unfinished discussion on so-and-so reopening a legitimate legal procedure of a complete assembly. The case has not been decided.*";
P_HTM[12384]="*Tassa pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapemi, na tasmiṃ sammukhībhūte pātimokkhaṃ uddisitabbanti—**I cancel his hearing of the Monastic Code. The Monastic Code should not be recited in his presence.’*";
P_HTM[12385]="*dhammikaṃ pātimokkhaṭṭhapanaṃ’.**This cancellation of the Monastic Code is legitimate.*";
P_HTM[12386]="*Kathaṃ sīlavipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkito hoti?**“And how is failure in morality seen, heard, or suspected?*";
P_HTM[12387]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yehi ākārehi yehi liṅgehi yehi nimittehi sīlavipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkito hoti, tehi ākārehi tehi liṅgehi tehi nimittehi bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ passati sīlavipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkitaṃ.**A monk sees in a monk the characteristics and signs of someone who has been seen, heard, or suspected of failure in morality.*";
P_HTM[12388]="*Na heva kho bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ passati sīlavipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkitaṃ, api ca añño bhikkhu bhikkhussa āroceti—**Or a monk doesn’t see a monk who has been seen, heard, or suspected of failure in morality, but another monk informs him,*";
P_HTM[12389]="*‘itthannāmo, āvuso, bhikkhu sīlavipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkito’ti.**‘Monk so-and-so has been seen, heard, or suspected of failure in morality.’*";
P_HTM[12390]="*Na heva kho bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ passati sīlavipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkitaṃ, nāpi añño bhikkhu bhikkhussa āroceti—**Or a monk doesn’t see a monk who has been seen, heard, or suspected of failure in morality, nor does another monk inform him,*";
P_HTM[12391]="*‘itthannāmo, āvuso, bhikkhu sīlavipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkito’ti, api ca sova bhikkhu bhikkhussa āroceti—**but the monk himself informs him,*";
P_HTM[12392]="*‘ahaṃ, āvuso, sīlavipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkitomhī’ti.**‘I have been seen, heard, or suspected of failure in morality.’*";
P_HTM[12393]="*Ākaṅkhamāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tena diṭṭhena tena sutena tāya parisaṅkāya tadahuposathe cātuddase vā pannarase vā tasmiṃ puggale sammukhībhūte saṅghamajjhe udāhareyya—**Then, on the observance day, whether the fourteenth or the fifteenth, he may if he wishes, based on what he’s seen, heard, or suspects, announce in the midst of the Sangha and in the presence of that person:*";
P_HTM[12394]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[12395]="*Itthannāmo puggalo sīlavipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkito, tassa pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapemi, na tasmiṃ sammukhībhūte pātimokkhaṃ uddisitabbanti—**So-and-so has been seen, heard, or suspected of failure in morality. I cancel his hearing of the Monastic Code. The Monastic Code should not be recited in his presence.’*";
P_HTM[12396]="*dhammikaṃ pātimokkhaṭṭhapanaṃ’.**This cancellation of the Monastic Code is legitimate.*";
P_HTM[12397]="*Kathaṃ ācāravipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkito hoti?**“And how is failure in conduct seen, heard, or suspected?*";
P_HTM[12398]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yehi ākārehi yehi liṅgehi yehi nimittehi ācāravipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkito hoti tehi ākārehi tehi liṅgehi tehi nimittehi bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ passati ācāravipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkitaṃ.**A monk sees in a monk the characteristics and signs of someone who has been seen, heard, or suspected of failure in conduct.*";
P_HTM[12399]="*Na heva kho bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ passati ācāravipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkitaṃ, api ca añño bhikkhu bhikkhussa āroceti—**Or a monk doesn’t see a monk who has been seen, heard, or suspected of failure in conduct, but another monk informs him,*";
P_HTM[12400]="*‘itthannāmo, āvuso, bhikkhu ācāravipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkito’ti.**‘Monk so-and-so has been seen, heard, or suspected of failure in conduct.’*";
P_HTM[12401]="*Na heva kho bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ passati ācāravipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkitaṃ, nāpi añño bhikkhu bhikkhussa āroceti—**Or a monk doesn’t see a monk who has been seen, heard, or suspected of failure in conduct, nor does another monk inform him,*";
P_HTM[12402]="*‘itthannāmo, āvuso, bhikkhu ācāravipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkito’ti, api ca sova bhikkhu bhikkhussa āroceti—**but the monk himself informs him,*";
P_HTM[12403]="*‘ahaṃ, āvuso, ācāravipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkitomhī’ti.**‘I have been seen, heard, or suspected of failure in conduct.’*";
P_HTM[12404]="*Ākaṅkhamāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tena diṭṭhena tena sutena tāya parisaṅkāya tadahuposathe cātuddase vā pannarase vā tasmiṃ puggale sammukhībhūte saṅghamajjhe udāhareyya—**Then, on the observance day, whether the fourteenth or the fifteenth, he may if he wishes, based on what he’s seen, heard, or suspects, announce in the midst of the Sangha and in the presence of that person:*";
P_HTM[12405]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[12406]="*Itthannāmo puggalo ācāravipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkito, tassa pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapemi, na tasmiṃ sammukhībhūte pātimokkhaṃ uddisitabbanti—**So-and-so has been seen, heard, or suspected of failure in conduct. I cancel his hearing of the Monastic Code. The Monastic Code should not be recited in his presence.’*";
P_HTM[12407]="*dhammikaṃ pātimokkhaṭṭhapanaṃ’.**This cancellation of the Monastic Code is legitimate.*";
P_HTM[12408]="*Kathaṃ diṭṭhivipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkito hoti?**“And how is failure in view seen, heard, or suspected?*";
P_HTM[12409]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yehi ākārehi yehi liṅgehi yehi nimittehi diṭṭhivipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkito hoti, tehi ākārehi tehi liṅgehi tehi nimittehi bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ passati diṭṭhivipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkitaṃ.**A monk sees in a monk the characteristics and signs of someone who has been seen, heard, or suspected of failure in view.*";
P_HTM[12410]="*Na heva kho bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ passati diṭṭhivipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkitaṃ, api ca añño bhikkhu bhikkhussa āroceti—**Or a monk doesn’t see a monk who has been seen, heard, or suspected of failure in view, but another monk informs him,*";
P_HTM[12411]="*‘itthannāmo, āvuso, bhikkhu diṭṭhivipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkito’ti.**‘Monk so-and-so has been seen, heard, or suspected of failure in view.’*";
P_HTM[12412]="*Na heva kho bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ passati diṭṭhivipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkitaṃ, nāpi añño bhikkhu bhikkhussa āroceti—**Or a monk doesn’t see a monk who has been seen, heard, or suspected of failure in view, nor does another monk inform him,*";
P_HTM[12413]="*‘itthannāmo, āvuso, bhikkhu diṭṭhivipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkito’ti, api ca sova bhikkhu bhikkhussa āroceti—**but the monk himself informs him,*";
P_HTM[12414]="*‘ahaṃ, āvuso, diṭṭhivipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkitomhī’ti.**‘I have been seen, heard, or suspected of failure in view.’*";
P_HTM[12415]="*Ākaṅkhamāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tena diṭṭhena tena sutena tāya parisaṅkāya tadahuposathe cātuddase vā pannarase vā tasmiṃ puggale sammukhībhūte saṅghamajjhe udāhareyya—**Then, on the observance day, whether the fourteenth or the fifteenth, he may if he wishes, based on what he’s seen, heard, or suspects, announce in the midst of the Sangha and in the presence of that person:*";
P_HTM[12416]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[12417]="*Itthannāmo puggalo diṭṭhivipattiyā diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkito, tassa pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapemi, na tasmiṃ sammukhībhūte pātimokkhaṃ uddisitabbanti—**So-and-so has been seen, heard, or suspected of failure in view. I cancel his hearing of the Monastic Code. The Monastic Code should not be recited in his presence.’*";
P_HTM[12418]="*dhammikaṃ pātimokkhaṭṭhapanaṃ’.**This cancellation of the Monastic Code is legitimate.*";
P_HTM[12419]="*Imāni dasa dhammikāni pātimokkhaṭṭhapanānī”ti.**These are the ten legitimate cancellations of the Monastic Code.”*";
P_HTM[12420]="*Paṭhamabhāṇavāro niṭṭhito.**The first section for recitation is finished.*";
P_HTM[12421]="*7. Attādānaaṅga**7. The qualities needed to raise an issue*";
P_HTM[12422]="*Atha kho āyasmā upāli yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Venerable Upāli went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[12423]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā upāli bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[12424]="*“attādānaṃ ādātukāmena, bhante, bhikkhunā katamaṅgasamannāgataṃ attādānaṃ ādātabban”ti?**“Venerable Sir, if a monk wishes to raise an issue, what factors should be fulfilled?”*";
P_HTM[12425]="*“Attādānaṃ ādātukāmena, upāli, bhikkhunā pañcaṅgasamannāgataṃ attādānaṃ ādātabbaṃ.**“If a monk who wishes to raise an issue, five factors should be fulfilled:*";
P_HTM[12426]="*Attādānaṃ ādātukāmena, upāli, bhikkhunā evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ—**He should reflect*";
P_HTM[12427]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ imaṃ attādānaṃ ādātukāmo, kālo nu kho imaṃ attādānaṃ ādātuṃ udāhu no’ti?**whether or not it’s the right time to raise the issue.*";
P_HTM[12428]="*Sace, upāli, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti—**If he knows*";
P_HTM[12429]="*‘akālo imaṃ attādānaṃ ādātuṃ, no kālo’ti, na taṃ, upāli, attādānaṃ ādātabbaṃ.**it’s the wrong time, he shouldn’t raise it.*";
P_HTM[12430]="*Sace panupāli, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti—**But if he knows*";
P_HTM[12431]="*‘kālo imaṃ attādānaṃ ādātuṃ, no akālo’ti, tenupāli, bhikkhunā uttari paccavekkhitabbaṃ—**it’s the right time, he should reflect further*";
P_HTM[12432]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ imaṃ attādānaṃ ādātukāmo, bhūtaṃ nu kho idaṃ attādānaṃ udāhu no’ti?**whether or not it’s a real issue.*";
P_HTM[12433]="*Sace, upāli, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti—**If he knows*";
P_HTM[12434]="*‘abhūtaṃ idaṃ attādānaṃ, no bhūtan’ti, na taṃ, upāli, attādānaṃ ādātabbaṃ.**it’s not, he shouldn’t raise it.*";
P_HTM[12435]="*Sace panupāli, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti—**But if he knows*";
P_HTM[12436]="*‘bhūtaṃ idaṃ attādānaṃ, no abhūtan’ti, tenupāli, bhikkhunā uttari paccavekkhitabbaṃ—**it’s real, he should reflect further*";
P_HTM[12437]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ imaṃ attādānaṃ ādātukāmo, atthasañhitaṃ nu kho idaṃ attādānaṃ udāhu no’ti?**whether or not raising the issue will be beneficial.*";
P_HTM[12438]="*Sace, upāli, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti—**If he knows*";
P_HTM[12439]="*‘anatthasañhitaṃ idaṃ attādānaṃ, no atthasañhitan’ti, na taṃ, upāli, attādānaṃ ādātabbaṃ.**it won’t, he shouldn’t raise it.*";
P_HTM[12440]="*Sace panupāli, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti—**But if he knows*";
P_HTM[12441]="*‘atthasañhitaṃ idaṃ attādānaṃ, no anatthasañhitan’ti, tenupāli, bhikkhunā uttari paccavekkhitabbaṃ—**it will be beneficial, he should reflect further*";
P_HTM[12442]="*‘imaṃ kho ahaṃ attādānaṃ ādiyamāno labhissāmi sandiṭṭhe sambhatte bhikkhū dhammato vinayato pakkhe udāhu no’ti?**whether or not the monks who are on the side of the Teaching and the Monastic Law will take his side.*";
P_HTM[12443]="*Sace, upāli, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti—**If he knows*";
P_HTM[12444]="*‘imaṃ kho ahaṃ attādānaṃ ādiyamāno na labhissāmi sandiṭṭhe sambhatte bhikkhū dhammato vinayato pakkhe’ti, na taṃ, upāli, attādānaṃ ādātabbaṃ.**that they won’t, he shouldn’t raise it.*";
P_HTM[12445]="*Sace panupāli, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti—**But if he knows*";
P_HTM[12446]="*‘imaṃ kho ahaṃ attādānaṃ ādiyamāno labhissāmi sandiṭṭhe sambhatte bhikkhū dhammato vinayato pakkhe’ti, tenupāli, bhikkhunā uttari paccavekkhitabbaṃ—**they will take his side, he should reflect further*";
P_HTM[12447]="*‘imaṃ kho me attādānaṃ ādiyato bhavissati saṅghassa tatonidānaṃ bhaṇḍanaṃ kalaho viggaho vivādo saṅghabhedo saṅgharāji saṅghavavatthānaṃ saṅghanānākaraṇaṃ udāhu no’ti?**whether or not raising the issue will lead to arguments and disputes, to fracture and schism in the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[12448]="*Sace upāli, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti—**If he knows*";
P_HTM[12449]="*‘imaṃ kho me attādānaṃ ādiyato bhavissati saṅghassa tatonidānaṃ bhaṇḍanaṃ kalaho viggaho vivādo saṅghabhedo saṅgharāji saṅghavavatthānaṃ saṅghanānākaraṇan’ti, na taṃ, upāli, attādānaṃ ādātabbaṃ.**it will, he shouldn’t raise it.*";
P_HTM[12450]="*Sace panupāli, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti—**But if he knows*";
P_HTM[12451]="*‘imaṃ kho me attādānaṃ ādiyato na bhavissati saṅghassa tatonidānaṃ bhaṇḍanaṃ kalaho viggaho vivādo saṅghabhedo saṅgharāji saṅghavavatthānaṃ saṅghanānākaraṇan’ti, ādātabbaṃ taṃ, upāli, attādānaṃ.**it won’t, he may raise the issue.*";
P_HTM[12452]="*Evaṃ pañcaṅgasamannāgataṃ kho, upāli, attādānaṃ ādinnaṃ, pacchāpi avippaṭisārakaraṃ bhavissatī”ti.**In this way, when five factors are fulfilled, he won’t regret raising it.”*";
P_HTM[12453]="*8. Codakenapaccavekkhitabbadhamma**8. The qualities to be reflected upon by one who accuses another*";
P_HTM[12454]="*“Codakena, bhante, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena kati dhamme ajjhattaṃ paccavekkhitvā paro codetabbo”ti?**“Sir, how many qualities should a monk see in himself before accusing another?”*";
P_HTM[12455]="*“Codakena, upāli, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ paccavekkhitvā paro codetabbo.**“A monk should see five qualities in himself before accusing another.*";
P_HTM[12456]="*Codakena, upāli, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ—**Before accusing another, a monk should reflect,*";
P_HTM[12457]="*‘parisuddhakāyasamācāro nu khomhi, parisuddhenamhi kāyasamācārena samannāgato—acchiddena appaṭimaṃsena? Saṃvijjati nu kho me eso dhammo udāhu no’ti?**‘Is my bodily conduct pure and faultless? Is this quality found in me or not?’*";
P_HTM[12458]="*No ce, upāli, bhikkhu parisuddhakāyasamācāro hoti, parisuddhena kāyasamācārena samannāgato—acchiddena appaṭimaṃsena, tassa bhavanti vattāro—**If it’s not, there will be those who say,*";
P_HTM[12459]="*‘iṅgha tāva āyasmā kāyikaṃ sikkhassū’ti. Itissa bhavanti vattāro.**‘Please train your own bodily conduct first.’*";
P_HTM[12460]="*Puna caparaṃ, upāli, codakena bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ—**Before accusing another, a monk should reflect,*";
P_HTM[12461]="*‘parisuddhavacīsamācāro nu khomhi, parisuddhenamhi vacīsamācārena samannāgato—acchiddena appaṭimaṃsena? Saṃvijjati nu kho me eso dhammo udāhu no’ti?**‘Is my verbal conduct pure and faultless? Is this quality found in me or not?’*";
P_HTM[12462]="*No ce, upāli, bhikkhu parisuddhavacīsamācāro hoti, parisuddhena vacīsamācārena samannāgato—**If it’s not,*";
P_HTM[12463]="*acchiddena appaṭimaṃsena, tassa bhavanti vattāro—**there will be those who say,*";
P_HTM[12464]="*‘iṅgha tāva āyasmā vācasikaṃ sikkhassū’ti. Itissa bhavanti vattāro.**‘Please train your own verbal conduct first.’*";
P_HTM[12465]="*Puna caparaṃ, upāli, codakena bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ—**Before accusing another, a monk should reflect,*";
P_HTM[12466]="*‘mettaṃ nu kho me cittaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ sabrahmacārīsu anāghātaṃ, saṃvijjati nu kho me eso dhammo udāhu no’ti?**‘Do I have a mind of good will toward my fellow monastics? Am I free from ill will toward them? Is this quality found in me or not?’*";
P_HTM[12467]="*No ce, upāli, bhikkhuno mettacittaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti sabrahmacārīsu anāghātaṃ, tassa bhavanti vattāro—**If it’s not, there will be those who say,*";
P_HTM[12468]="*‘iṅgha tāva āyasmā sabrahmacārīsu mettacittaṃ upaṭṭhāpehī’ti. Itissa bhavanti vattāro.**‘Please set up a mind of good will toward your fellow monastics first.’*";
P_HTM[12469]="*Puna caparaṃ, upāli, codakena bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ—**Before accusing another, a monk should reflect,*";
P_HTM[12470]="*‘bahussuto nu khomhi, sutadharo, sutasannicayo? Ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpā me dhammā bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā? Saṃvijjati nu kho me eso dhammo udāhu no’ti?**‘Have I learned much and do I retain and accumulate what I’ve learned? Those teachings that are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, that have a true goal and are well articulated, and that set out the perfectly complete and pure spiritual life—have I learned many such teachings, retained them in mind, recited them verbally, mentally investigated them, and penetrated them well by view? Is this quality found in me or not?’*";
P_HTM[12471]="*No ce, upāli, bhikkhu bahussuto hoti, sutadharo, sutasannicayo; ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpassa dhammā na bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā, tassa bhavanti vattāro—**If it’s not, there will be those who say,*";
P_HTM[12472]="*‘iṅgha tāva āyasmā āgamaṃ pariyāpuṇassū’ti. Itissa bhavanti vattāro.**‘Please learn the tradition first.’*";
P_HTM[12473]="*Puna caparaṃ, upāli, codakena bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena evaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ—**Before accusing another, a monk should reflect,*";
P_HTM[12474]="*‘ubhayāni kho me pātimokkhāni vitthārena svāgatāni honti, suvibhattāni, suppavattīni, suvinicchitāni, suttaso, anubyañjanaso? Saṃvijjati nu kho me eso dhammo udāhu no’ti?**‘Have I properly learned both Monastic Codes in detail; have I analyzed them well, thoroughly mastered them, and investigated them well, both in terms of the rules and their detailed exposition? Is this quality found in me or not?’*";
P_HTM[12475]="*No ce, upāli, bhikkhuno ubhayāni pātimokkhāni vitthārena svāgatāni honti, suvibhattāni, suppavattīni, suvinicchitāni, suttaso, anubyañjanaso, ‘idaṃ panāvuso, kattha vuttaṃ bhagavatā’ti, iti puṭṭho na sampāyati, tassa bhavanti vattāro—**If it’s not, then when he is asked, ‘Where was this said by the Buddha?’ he won’t be able to reply. And there will be those who say,*";
P_HTM[12476]="*‘iṅgha tāva āyasmā vinayaṃ pariyāpuṇassū’ti. Itissa bhavanti vattāro.**‘Please learn the Monastic Law first.’*";
P_HTM[12477]="*Codakenupāli, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena ime pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ paccavekkhitvā paro codetabbo”ti.**A monk should see these five qualities in himself before accusing another.”*";
P_HTM[12478]="*9. Codakenaupaṭṭhāpetabbadhamma**9. The qualities to be set up by one who accuses another*";
P_HTM[12479]="*“Codakena, bhante, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena kati dhamme ajjhattaṃ upaṭṭhāpetvā paro codetabbo”ti?**“Sir, how many qualities should a monk set up in himself before accusing another?”*";
P_HTM[12480]="*“Codakenupāli, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ upaṭṭhāpetvā paro codetabbo—**“A monk should set up five qualities in himself before accusing another. He should think,*";
P_HTM[12481]="*kālena vakkhāmi, no akālena;**‘I’ll speak at an appropriate time, not at an inappropriate one;*";
P_HTM[12482]="*bhūtena vakkhāmi, no abhūtena;**I’ll speak the truth, not falsehood;*";
P_HTM[12483]="*saṇhena vakkhāmi, no pharusena;**I’ll speak gently, not harshly;*";
P_HTM[12484]="*atthasaṃhitena vakkhāmi, no anatthasaṃhitena;**I’ll speak what’s beneficial, not what’s unbeneficial;*";
P_HTM[12485]="*mettacitto vakkhāmi, no dosantaroti.**I’ll speak with a mind of good will, not with internal ill will.’”*";
P_HTM[12486]="*Codakenupāli, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena ime pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ upaṭṭhāpetvā paro codetabbo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[12487]="*10. Codakacuditakapaṭisaṃyuttakathā**10. Discussion on the one who accuses and the one who is accused*";
P_HTM[12488]="*“Adhammacodakassa, bhante, bhikkhuno katihākārehi vippaṭisāro upadahātabbo”ti?**“Sir, if a monk accuses another illegitimately, in how many ways should regret be aroused in him?”*";
P_HTM[12489]="*“Adhammacodakassa, upāli, bhikkhuno pañcahākārehi vippaṭisāro upadahātabbo—**“Regret should be aroused in him in five ways:*";
P_HTM[12490]="*akālenāyasmā codesi, no kālena, alaṃ te vippaṭisārāya;**‘Venerable, you’re accusing at the wrong time, not the right time; it’s appropriate for you to have regret.*";
P_HTM[12491]="*abhūtenāyasmā codesi, no bhūtena, alaṃ te vippaṭisārāya;**You’re accusing falsely, not truthfully; it’s appropriate for you to have regret.*";
P_HTM[12492]="*pharusenāyasmā codesi, no saṇhena, alaṃ te vippaṭisārāya;**You’re accusing harshly, not gently; it’s appropriate for you to have regret.*";
P_HTM[12493]="*anatthasaṃhitenāyasmā codesi, no atthasaṃhitena, alaṃ te vippaṭisārāya;**You’re accusing unbeneficially, not beneficially; it’s appropriate for you to have regret.*";
P_HTM[12494]="*dosantaro āyasmā codesi, no mettacitto, alaṃ te vippaṭisārāyāti.**You’re accusing with internal ill will, not with a mind of good will; it’s appropriate for you to have regret.’*";
P_HTM[12495]="*Adhammacodakassa, upāli, bhikkhuno imehi pañcahākārehi vippaṭisāro upadahātabbo.**These are the five ways regret should be aroused in a monk who accuses another illegitimately.*";
P_HTM[12496]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**For what reason?*";
P_HTM[12497]="*Yathā na aññopi bhikkhu abhūtena codetabbaṃ maññeyyā”ti.**So that other monks won’t think to accuse others falsely.”*";
P_HTM[12498]="*“Adhammacuditassa pana, bhante, bhikkhuno katihākārehi avippaṭisāro upadahātabbo”ti?**“And if a monk has been accused illegitimately, in how many ways should non-regret be aroused in him?”*";
P_HTM[12499]="*“Adhammacuditassa, upāli, bhikkhuno pañcahākārehi avippaṭisāro upadahātabbo—**“Non-regret should be aroused in him in five ways:*";
P_HTM[12500]="*akālenāyasmā cudito, no kālena, alaṃ te avippaṭisārāya;**‘Venerable, you have been accused at the wrong time, not the right time; there is no need for you to have regret.*";
P_HTM[12501]="*abhūtenāyasmā cudito, no bhūtena, alaṃ te avippaṭisārāya;**You have been accused falsely, not truthfully; there is no need for you to have regret.*";
P_HTM[12502]="*pharusenāyasmā cudito, no saṇhena, alaṃ te avippaṭisārāya;**You have been accused harshly, not gently; there is no need for you to have regret.*";
P_HTM[12503]="*anatthasaṃhitenāyasmā cudito, no atthasaṃhitena, alaṃ te avippaṭisārāya;**You have been accused unbeneficially, not beneficially; there is no need for you to have regret.*";
P_HTM[12504]="*dosantarenāyasmā cudito, no mettacittena, alaṃ te avippaṭisārāyāti.**You have been accused with internal ill will, not with a mind of good will; there is no need for you to have regret.’”*";
P_HTM[12505]="*Adhammacuditassa, upāli, bhikkhuno imehi pañcahākārehi avippaṭisāro upadahātabbo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[12506]="*“Dhammacodakassa, bhante, bhikkhuno katihākārehi avippaṭisāro upadahātabbo”ti?**“And if a monk accuses another legitimately, in how many ways should non-regret be aroused in him?”*";
P_HTM[12507]="*“Dhammacodakassa, upāli, bhikkhuno pañcahākārehi avippaṭisāro upadahātabbo—**“Non-regret should be aroused in him in five ways:*";
P_HTM[12508]="*kālenāyasmā codesi, no akālena, alaṃ te avippaṭisārāya;**‘Venerable, you’re accusing at the right time, not the wrong time; there is no need for you to have regret.*";
P_HTM[12509]="*bhūtenāyasmā codesi, no abhūtena, alaṃ te avippaṭisārāya;**You’re accusing truthfully, not falsely; there is no need for you to have regret.*";
P_HTM[12510]="*saṇhenāyasmā codesi, no pharusena, alaṃ te avippaṭisārāya;**You’re accusing gently, not harshly; there is no need for you to have regret.*";
P_HTM[12511]="*atthasaṃhitenāyasmā codesi, no anatthasaṃhitena, alaṃ te avippaṭisārāya;**You’re accusing beneficially, not unbeneficially; there is no need for you to have regret.*";
P_HTM[12512]="*mettacitto āyasmā codesi, no dosantaro, alaṃ te avippaṭisārāyāti.**You’re accusing with a mind of good will, not with internal ill will; there is no need for you to have regret.’*";
P_HTM[12513]="*Dhammacodakassa, upāli, bhikkhuno imehi pañcahākārehi avippaṭisāro upadahātabbo.**These are the five ways non-regret should be aroused in a monk who accuses another legitimately.*";
P_HTM[12514]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**For what reason?*";
P_HTM[12515]="*Yathā aññopi bhikkhu bhūtena codetabbaṃ maññeyyā”ti.**So that other monks will think to accuse others truthfully.”*";
P_HTM[12516]="*“Dhammacuditassa pana, bhante, bhikkhuno katihākārehi vippaṭisāro upadahātabbo”ti?**“And if a monk has been accused legitimately, in how many ways should regret be aroused in him?”*";
P_HTM[12517]="*“Dhammacuditassa, upāli, bhikkhuno pañcahākārehi vippaṭisāro upadahātabbo—**“Regret should be aroused in him in five ways:*";
P_HTM[12518]="*kālenāyasmā cudito, no akālena, alaṃ te vippaṭisārāya;**‘Venerable, you have been accused at the right time, not the wrong time; it’s appropriate for you to have regret.*";
P_HTM[12519]="*bhūtenāyasmā cudito, no abhūtena, alaṃ te vippaṭisārāya;**You have been accused truthfully, not falsely; it’s appropriate for you to have regret.*";
P_HTM[12520]="*saṇhenāyasmā cudito, no pharusena, alaṃ te vippaṭisārāya;**You have been accused gently, not harshly; it’s appropriate for you to have regret.*";
P_HTM[12521]="*atthasaṃhitenāyasmā cudito, no anatthasaṃhitena, alaṃ te vippaṭisārāya;**You have been accused beneficially, not unbeneficially; it’s appropriate for you to have regret.*";
P_HTM[12522]="*mettacittenāyasmā cudito, no dosantarena, alaṃ te vippaṭisārāyāti.**You have been accused with a mind of good will, not with internal ill will; it’s appropriate for you to have regret.’”*";
P_HTM[12523]="*Dhammacuditassa, upāli, bhikkhuno imehi pañcahākārehi vippaṭisāro upadahātabbo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[12524]="*“Codakena, bhante, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena kati dhamme ajjhattaṃ manasi karitvā paro codetabbo”ti?**“And, Sir, how many qualities should a monk attend to in himself before accusing another?”*";
P_HTM[12525]="*“Codakenupāli, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ manasi karitvā paro codetabbo—**“A monk should attend to five qualities in himself before accusing another:*";
P_HTM[12526]="*kāruññatā, hitesitā, anukampitā, āpattivuṭṭhānatā, vinayapurekkhāratāti.**compassion, being of benefit, sympathy, the idea of clearing offenses, and the idea of giving priority to the training.”*";
P_HTM[12527]="*Codakenupāli, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena ime pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ manasi karitvā paro codetabbo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[12528]="*“Cuditena pana, bhante, bhikkhunā katisu dhammesu patiṭṭhātabban”ti?**“And how many qualities should a monk who has been accused set up?”*";
P_HTM[12529]="*“Cuditenupāli, bhikkhunā dvīsu dhammesu patiṭṭhātabbaṃ—**“A monk who has been accused should set up two qualities:*";
P_HTM[12530]="*sacce ca akuppe cā”ti.**truth and composure.”*";
P_HTM[12531]="*Dutiyabhāṇavāro niṭṭhito.**The second section for recitation is finished.*";
P_HTM[12532]="*Pātimokkhaṭṭhapanakkhandhako navamo.**The ninth chapter on the cancellation of the Monastic Code is finished.*";
P_HTM[12533]="*Imamhi khandhake vatthū tiṃsa.**In this chapter there are thirty topics.*";
P_HTM[12534]="*Tassuddānaṃ* **";
P_HTM[12535]="*Uposathe yāvatikaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[12536]="*pāpabhikkhu na nikkhami;* **";
P_HTM[12537]="*Moggallānena nicchuddho,* **";
P_HTM[12538]="*accherā jinasāsane.* **";
P_HTM[12539]="*Ninnonupubbasikkhā ca,* **";
P_HTM[12540]="*ṭhitadhammo nātikkamma;* **";
P_HTM[12541]="*Kuṇapukkhipati saṅgho,* **";
P_HTM[12542]="*savantiyo jahanti ca.* **";
P_HTM[12543]="*Savanti parinibbanti,* **";
P_HTM[12544]="*ekarasa vimutti ca;* **";
P_HTM[12545]="*Bahu dhammavinayopi,* **";
P_HTM[12546]="*bhūtaṭṭhāriyapuggalā.* **";
P_HTM[12547]="*Samuddaṃ upamaṃ katvā,* **";
P_HTM[12548]="*vācesi sāsane guṇaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[12549]="*Uposathe pātimokkhaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[12550]="*na amhe koci jānāti.* **";
P_HTM[12551]="*Paṭikacceva ujjhanti,* **";
P_HTM[12552]="*eko dve tīṇi cattāri;* **";
P_HTM[12553]="*Pañca cha satta aṭṭhāni,* **";
P_HTM[12554]="*navā ca dasamāni ca.* **";
P_HTM[12555]="*Sīlaācāradiṭṭhi ca,* **";
P_HTM[12556]="*ājīvaṃ catubhāgike;* **";
P_HTM[12557]="*Pārājikañca saṅghādi,* **";
P_HTM[12558]="*pācitti pāṭidesani.* **";
P_HTM[12559]="*Dukkaṭaṃ pañcabhāgesu,* **";
P_HTM[12560]="*sīlācāravipatti ca;* **";
P_HTM[12561]="*Akatāya katāya ca,* **";
P_HTM[12562]="*chabhāgesu yathāvidhi.* **";
P_HTM[12563]="*Pārājikañca saṅghādi,* **";
P_HTM[12564]="*thullaṃ pācittiyena ca;* **";
P_HTM[12565]="*Pāṭidesaniyañceva,* **";
P_HTM[12566]="*dukkaṭañca dubbhāsitaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[12567]="*Sīlācāravipatti ca,* **";
P_HTM[12568]="*Diṭṭhiājīvavipatti;* **";
P_HTM[12569]="*Yā ca aṭṭhā katākate,* **";
P_HTM[12570]="*Tenetā sīlācāradiṭṭhiyā.* **";
P_HTM[12571]="*Akatāya katāyāpi,* **";
P_HTM[12572]="*katākatāyameva ca;* **";
P_HTM[12573]="*Evaṃ navavidhā vuttā,* **";
P_HTM[12574]="*yathābhūtena ñāyato.* **";
P_HTM[12575]="*Pārājiko vippakatā,* **";
P_HTM[12576]="*paccakkhāto tatheva ca;* **";
P_HTM[12577]="*Upeti paccādiyati,* **";
P_HTM[12578]="*paccādānakathā ca yā.* **";
P_HTM[12579]="*Sīlācāravipatti ca,* **";
P_HTM[12580]="*tathā diṭṭhivipattiyā;* **";
P_HTM[12581]="*Diṭṭhasutaparisaṅkitaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[12582]="*dasadhā taṃ vijānātha.* **";
P_HTM[12583]="*Bhikkhu vipassati bhikkhuṃ,* **";
P_HTM[12584]="*añño cārocayāti taṃ;* **";
P_HTM[12585]="*Soyeva tassa akkhāti,* **";
P_HTM[12586]="*pātimokkhaṃ ṭhapeti so.* **";
P_HTM[12587]="*Vuṭṭhāti antarāyena,* **";
P_HTM[12588]="*Rājacoraggudakā ca;* **";
P_HTM[12589]="*Manussaamanussā ca,* **";
P_HTM[12590]="*Vāḷasarīsapā jīvibrahmaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[12591]="*Dasannamaññatarena,* **";
P_HTM[12592]="*tasmiṃ aññataresu vā;* **";
P_HTM[12593]="*Dhammikādhammikā ceva,* **";
P_HTM[12594]="*yathā maggena jānātha.* **";
P_HTM[12595]="*Kālabhūtatthasaṃhitaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[12596]="*labhissāmi bhavissati;* **";
P_HTM[12597]="*Kāyavācasikā mettā,* **";
P_HTM[12598]="*bāhusaccaṃ ubhayāni.* **";
P_HTM[12599]="*Kālabhūtena saṇhena,* **";
P_HTM[12600]="*atthamettena codaye;* **";
P_HTM[12601]="*Vippaṭisāradhammena,* **";
P_HTM[12602]="*tathā vācā vinodaye.* **";
P_HTM[12603]="*Dhammacodacuditassa,* **";
P_HTM[12604]="*vinodeti vippaṭisāro;* **";
P_HTM[12605]="*Karuṇā hitānukampi,* **";
P_HTM[12606]="*vuṭṭhānapurekkhārato.* **";
P_HTM[12607]="*Codakassa paṭipatti,* **";
P_HTM[12608]="*sambuddhena pakāsitā;* **";
P_HTM[12609]="*Sacce ceva akuppe ca,* **";
P_HTM[12610]="*cuditasseva dhammatāti.* **";
P_HTM[12611]="*Pātimokkhaṭṭhapanakkhandhako niṭṭhito.**The chapter on the cancellation of the Monastic Code is finished.*";
P_HTM[12612]="*10. Bhikkhunikkhandhaka **10.  The chapter on nuns *";
P_HTM[12613]="*1. Mahāpajāpatigotamīvatthu**1. The account of Mahāpajāpati Gotamī*";
P_HTM[12614]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the Sakyan country in Banyan Tree Monastery at Kapilavatthu.*";
P_HTM[12615]="*Atha kho mahāpajāpati gotamī yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi.**At this time Mahāpajāpati Gotamī went to the Buddha, bowed down to him,*";
P_HTM[12616]="*Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho mahāpajāpati gotamī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[12617]="*“sādhu, bhante, labheyya mātugāmo tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjan”ti.**“It would be good, Venerable Sir, if women were allowed to go forth into homelessness on the spiritual path made known by the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[12618]="*“Alaṃ, gotami, mā te rucci mātugāmassa tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjā”ti.**“Let it be, Gotami, don’t pursue this.”*";
P_HTM[12619]="*Dutiyampi kho …pe…**A second time*";
P_HTM[12620]="*tatiyampi kho mahāpajāpati gotamī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and a third time she asked*";
P_HTM[12621]="*“sādhu, bhante, labheyya mātugāmo tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjan”ti.**the same question*";
P_HTM[12622]="*“Alaṃ, gotami, mā te rucci mātugāmassa tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjā”ti.**and got the same reply.*";
P_HTM[12623]="*Atha kho mahāpajāpati gotamī—**She thought,*";
P_HTM[12624]="*“na bhagavā anujānāti mātugāmassa tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjan”ti—**“The Buddha doesn’t allow women to go forth,”*";
P_HTM[12625]="*dukkhī dummanā assumukhī rudamānā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**and sad and tearful she bowed down, circumambulated him with her right side toward him, and left.*";
P_HTM[12626]="*Atha kho bhagavā kapilavatthusmiṃ yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena vesālī tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**When the Buddha had stayed at Kapilavatthu for as long as he liked, he set out wandering toward Vesālī.*";
P_HTM[12627]="*Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena vesālī tadavasari.**When he eventually arrived,*";
P_HTM[12628]="*Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ.**he stayed in the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood.*";
P_HTM[12629]="*Atha kho mahāpajāpati gotamī kese chedāpetvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā sambahulāhi sākiyānīhi saddhiṃ yena vesālī tena pakkāmi.**In the meantime Mahāpajāpati had her hair cut off, put on ocher robes, and set out for Vesālī together with a number of Sakyan women.*";
P_HTM[12630]="*Anupubbena yena vesālī mahāvanaṃ kūṭāgārasālā tenupasaṅkami.**When she eventually arrived, she went to the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood.*";
P_HTM[12631]="*Atha kho mahāpajāpati gotamī sūnehi pādehi rajokiṇṇena gattena dukkhī dummanā assumukhī rudamānā bahidvārakoṭṭhake aṭṭhāsi.**And she stood outside the gateway, sad and tearful, covered in dust and her feet swollen.*";
P_HTM[12632]="*Addasā kho āyasmā ānando mahāpajāpatiṃ gotamiṃ sūnehi pādehi rajokiṇṇena gattena dukkhiṃ dummanaṃ assumukhiṃ rudamānaṃ bahidvārakoṭṭhake ṭhitaṃ.**Venerable Ānanda saw her there*";
P_HTM[12633]="*Disvāna mahāpajāpatiṃ gotamiṃ etadavoca—**and said to her,*";
P_HTM[12634]="*“kissa tvaṃ, gotami, sūnehi pādehi rajokiṇṇena gattena dukkhī dummanā assumukhī rudamānā bahidvārakoṭṭhake ṭhitā”ti?**“Why are you standing outside the gateway like this?”*";
P_HTM[12635]="*“Tathā hi pana, bhante ānanda, na bhagavā anujānāti mātugāmassa tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjan”ti.**“Because, Venerable Ānanda, the Buddha doesn’t allow women to go forth.”*";
P_HTM[12636]="*“Tena hi tvaṃ, gotami, muhuttaṃ idheva tāva hohi, yāvāhaṃ bhagavantaṃ yācāmi mātugāmassa tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjan”ti.**“Well then, Gotamī, please wait here for a moment, while I ask the Buddha to allow women to go forth.”*";
P_HTM[12637]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Venerable Ānanda went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[12638]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[12639]="*“esā, bhante, mahāpajāpati gotamī sūnehi pādehi rajokiṇṇena gattena dukkhī dummanā assumukhī rudamānā bahidvārakoṭṭhake ṭhitā—**“Sir, Mahāpajāpati Gotamī is standing outside the gateway, sad and tearful, covered in dust and her feet swollen.*";
P_HTM[12640]="*‘na bhagavā anujānāti mātugāmassa tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjan’ti.**She says you won’t allow women to go forth.*";
P_HTM[12641]="*Sādhu, bhante, labheyya mātugāmo tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjan”ti.**It would be good if women were allowed to go forth.”*";
P_HTM[12642]="*“Alaṃ, ānanda, mā te rucci mātugāmassa tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjā”ti.**“Let it be, Ānanda, don’t pursue this.”*";
P_HTM[12643]="*Dutiyampi kho …pe…**A second time*";
P_HTM[12644]="*tatiyampi kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and a third time he asked*";
P_HTM[12645]="*“sādhu, bhante, labheyya mātugāmo tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjan”ti.**the same question*";
P_HTM[12646]="*“Alaṃ, ānanda, mā te rucci mātugāmassa tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjā”ti.**and got the same reply.*";
P_HTM[12647]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando—**Ānanda thought,*";
P_HTM[12648]="*“na bhagavā anujānāti mātugāmassa tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjaṃ;**“The Buddha doesn’t allow women to go forth.*";
P_HTM[12649]="*yannūnāhaṃ aññenapi pariyāyena bhagavantaṃ yāceyyaṃ mātugāmassa tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjan”ti.**Why don’t I ask him in another way?”*";
P_HTM[12650]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**He then said,*";
P_HTM[12651]="*“bhabbo nu kho, bhante, mātugāmo tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitvā sotāpattiphalaṃ vā sakadāgāmiphalaṃ vā anāgāmiphalaṃ vā arahattaphalaṃ vā sacchikātun”ti?**“If women were allowed to go forth, would they be capable of realizing the fruit of stream-entry, the fruit of once-returning, the fruit of non-returning, and the fruit of perfection?”*";
P_HTM[12652]="*“Bhabbo, ānanda, mātugāmo tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitvā sotāpattiphalampi sakadāgāmiphalampi anāgāmiphalampi arahattaphalampi sacchikātun”ti.**“Yes, they would.”*";
P_HTM[12653]="*“Sace, bhante, bhabbo mātugāmo tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitvā sotāpattiphalampi sakadāgāmiphalampi anāgāmiphalampi arahattaphalampi sacchikātuṃ;**“If that’s so, Sir,*";
P_HTM[12654]="*bahūpakārā, bhante, mahāpajāpati gotamī bhagavato mātucchā āpādikā, posikā, khīrassa dāyikā, bhagavantaṃ janettiyā kālaṅkatāya thaññaṃ pāyesi;**and considering that Mahāpajāpati has been very helpful to you—she is your aunt who nurtured you, brought you up, and breastfed you when your own mother died—*";
P_HTM[12655]="*sādhu, bhante, labheyya mātugāmo tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjan”ti.**it would be good if women were allowed to go forth.”*";
P_HTM[12656]="*2. Aṭṭhagarudhamma**2. The eight important principles*";
P_HTM[12657]="*“Sace, ānanda, mahāpajāpati gotamī aṭṭha garudhamme paṭiggaṇhāti, sāvassā.**“Ānanda, if Mahāpajāpati accepts these eight important principles,*";
P_HTM[12658]="*Hotu upasampadā.**that will be her full ordination:*";
P_HTM[12659]="*Vassasatūpasampannāya bhikkhuniyā tadahupasampannassa bhikkhuno abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ añjalikammaṃ sāmīcikammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**A nun who has been fully ordained for a hundred years should bow down to a monk who was given the full ordination on that very day, and she should stand up for him, raise her joined palms to him, and do acts of respect toward him.*";
P_HTM[12660]="*Ayampi dhammo sakkatvā garukatvā mānetvā pūjetvā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyo.**This rule is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to be breached.*";
P_HTM[12661]="*Na bhikkhuniyā abhikkhuke āvāse vassaṃ vasitabbaṃ.**A nun should not spend the rainy-season residence in a monastery without monks.*";
P_HTM[12662]="*Ayampi dhammo sakkatvā garukatvā mānetvā pūjetvā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyo.**This rule too is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to be breached.*";
P_HTM[12663]="*Anvaddhamāsaṃ bhikkhuniyā bhikkhusaṅghato dve dhammā paccāsīsitabbā—**Every half-month a nun should seek two things from the Sangha of monks:*";
P_HTM[12664]="*uposathapucchakañca, ovādūpasaṅkamanañca.**asking it about the observance day and going to it for the instruction.*";
P_HTM[12665]="*Ayampi dhammo sakkatvā garukatvā mānetvā pūjetvā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyo.**This rule too is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to be breached.*";
P_HTM[12666]="*Vassaṃvuṭṭhāya bhikkhuniyā ubhatosaṅghe tīhi ṭhānehi pavāretabbaṃ—**A nun who has completed the rainy-season residence should invite correction from both Sanghas in regard to three things:*";
P_HTM[12667]="*diṭṭhena vā, sutena vā, parisaṅkāya vā.**what has been seen, what has been heard, and what has been suspected.*";
P_HTM[12668]="*Ayampi dhammo sakkatvā garukatvā mānetvā pūjetvā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyo.**This rule too is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to be breached.*";
P_HTM[12669]="*Garudhammaṃ ajjhāpannāya bhikkhuniyā ubhatosaṅghe pakkhamānattaṃ caritabbaṃ.**A nun who has committed a heavy offense must undertake a trial period for a half-month toward both Sanghas.*";
P_HTM[12670]="*Ayampi dhammo sakkatvā garukatvā mānetvā pūjetvā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyo.**This rule too is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to be breached.*";
P_HTM[12671]="*Dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhāya sikkhamānāya ubhatosaṅghe upasampadā pariyesitabbā.**A trainee nun who has trained in the six rules for two years may seek for full ordination in both Sanghas.*";
P_HTM[12672]="*Ayampi dhammo sakkatvā garukatvā mānetvā pūjetvā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyo.**This rule too is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to be breached.*";
P_HTM[12673]="*Na bhikkhuniyā kenaci pariyāyena bhikkhu akkositabbo paribhāsitabbo.**A nun may not in any way abuse or revile a monk.*";
P_HTM[12674]="*Ayampi dhammo sakkatvā garukatvā mānetvā pūjetvā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyo.**This rule too is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to be breached.*";
P_HTM[12675]="*Ajjatagge ovaṭo bhikkhunīnaṃ bhikkhūsu vacanapatho, anovaṭo bhikkhūnaṃ bhikkhunīsu vacanapatho.**From today onwards, nuns may not correct monks, but monks may correct nuns.*";
P_HTM[12676]="*Ayampi dhammo sakkatvā garukatvā mānetvā pūjetvā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyo.**This rule too is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to be breached.*";
P_HTM[12677]="*Sace, ānanda, mahāpajāpati gotamī ime aṭṭha garudhamme paṭiggaṇhāti, sāvassā hotu upasampadā”ti.**Ānanda, if Mahāpajāpati accepts these eight important principles, that will be her full ordination.”*";
P_HTM[12678]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato santike aṭṭha garudhamme uggahetvā yena mahāpajāpati gotamī tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā mahāpajāpatiṃ gotamiṃ etadavoca—**After learning these eight important principles from the Buddha, Ānanda went to Mahāpajāpati and said,*";
P_HTM[12679]="*“sace kho tvaṃ, gotami, aṭṭha garudhamme paṭiggaṇheyyāsi, sāva te bhavissati upasampadā.**“If you accept eight important principles, Gotami, that will be your full ordination.”*";
P_HTM[12680]="*Vassasatūpasampannāya bhikkhuniyā tadahupasampannassa bhikkhuno abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ añjalikammaṃ sāmīcikammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**And he told her the rules.*";
P_HTM[12681]="*Ayampi dhammo sakkatvā garukatvā mānetvā pūjetvā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyo.* **";
P_HTM[12682]="*Na bhikkhuniyā abhikkhuke āvāse vassaṃ vasitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[12683]="*Ayampi dhammo sakkatvā garukatvā mānetvā pūjetvā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyo.* **";
P_HTM[12684]="*Anvaddhamāsaṃ bhikkhuniyā bhikkhusaṅghato dve dhammā paccāsīsitabbā—* **";
P_HTM[12685]="*uposathapucchakañca, ovādūpasaṅkamanañca.* **";
P_HTM[12686]="*Ayampi dhammo sakkatvā garukatvā mānetvā pūjetvā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyo.* **";
P_HTM[12687]="*Vassaṃvuṭṭhāya bhikkhuniyā ubhatosaṅghe tīhi ṭhānehi pavāretabbaṃ—* **";
P_HTM[12688]="*diṭṭhena vā, sutena vā, parisaṅkāya vā.* **";
P_HTM[12689]="*Ayampi dhammo sakkatvā garukatvā mānetvā pūjetvā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyo.* **";
P_HTM[12690]="*Garudhammaṃ ajjhāpannāya bhikkhuniyā ubhatosaṅghe pakkhamānattaṃ caritabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[12691]="*Ayampi dhammo sakkatvā garukatvā mānetvā pūjetvā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyo.* **";
P_HTM[12692]="*Dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhāya sikkhamānāya ubhatosaṅghe upasampadā pariyesitabbā.* **";
P_HTM[12693]="*Ayampi dhammo sakkatvā garukatvā mānetvā pūjetvā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyo.* **";
P_HTM[12694]="*Na bhikkhuniyā kenaci pariyāyena bhikkhu akkositabbo paribhāsitabbo.* **";
P_HTM[12695]="*Ayampi dhammo sakkatvā garukatvā mānetvā pūjetvā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyo.* **";
P_HTM[12696]="*Ajjatagge ovaṭo bhikkhunīnaṃ bhikkhūsu vacanapatho, anovaṭo bhikkhūnaṃ bhikkhunīsu vacanapatho.* **";
P_HTM[12697]="*Ayampi dhammo sakkatvā garukatvā mānetvā pūjetvā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyo.* **";
P_HTM[12698]="*Sace kho tvaṃ, gotami, ime aṭṭha garudhamme paṭiggaṇheyyāsi, sāva te bhavissati upasampadā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[12699]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhante ānanda, itthī vā puriso vā daharo, yuvā, maṇḍanakajātiko sīsaṃnahāto uppalamālaṃ vā vassikamālaṃ vā atimuttakamālaṃ vā labhitvā ubhohi hatthehi paṭiggahetvā uttamaṅge sirasmiṃ patiṭṭhāpeyya;**She replied, “Just as a young woman or man—someone fond of adornments, who had just washed her hair—would receive a garland of lotuses, a garland of sandan flowers, or a garland of jasmine with both hands and place it on her head,*";
P_HTM[12700]="*evameva kho ahaṃ, bhante, ānanda ime aṭṭha garudhamme paṭiggaṇhāmi yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīye”ti.**so too, do I receive these eight important principles, not to be breached for life.”*";
P_HTM[12701]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Ānanda then went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[12702]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[12703]="*“paṭiggahitā, bhante, mahāpajāpatiyā gotamiyā aṭṭha garudhammā, upasampannā bhagavato mātucchā”ti.**“Sir, Mahāpajāpati has accepted the eight important principles. Your aunt has been ordained.”*";
P_HTM[12704]="*“Sace, ānanda, nālabhissa mātugāmo tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjaṃ, ciraṭṭhitikaṃ, ānanda, brahmacariyaṃ abhavissa, vassasahassaṃ saddhammo tiṭṭheyya.**“Ānanda, if women had not been allowed to go forth on this spiritual path made known by the Buddha, the spiritual life would have lasted a long time—the true Teaching would have lasted a thousand years.*";
P_HTM[12705]="*Yato ca kho, ānanda, mātugāmo tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito, na dāni, ānanda, brahmacariyaṃ ciraṭṭhitikaṃ bhavissati.**But since women have been allowed to go forth, the spiritual life won’t last long—*";
P_HTM[12706]="*Pañceva dāni, ānanda, vassasatāni saddhammo ṭhassati.**now the true Teaching will only last five hundred years.*";
P_HTM[12707]="*Seyyathāpi, ānanda, yāni kānici kulāni bahutthikāni appapurisakāni, tāni suppadhaṃsiyāni honti corehi kumbhathenakehi;**Just as families with many women and few men are easily robbed by thieves,*";
P_HTM[12708]="*evameva kho, ānanda, yasmiṃ dhammavinaye labhati mātugāmo agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjaṃ, na taṃ brahmacariyaṃ ciraṭṭhitikaṃ hoti.**so too, the spiritual life doesn’t last long on a spiritual path where women are allowed to go forth.*";
P_HTM[12709]="*Seyyathāpi, ānanda, sampanne sālikkhette setaṭṭikā nāma rogajāti nipatati, evaṃ taṃ sālikkhettaṃ na ciraṭṭhitikaṃ hoti;**Just as a ripe rice-field affected by whiteheads won’t last long,*";
P_HTM[12710]="*evameva kho, ānanda, yasmiṃ dhammavinaye labhati mātugāmo agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjaṃ, na taṃ brahmacariyaṃ ciraṭṭhitikaṃ hoti.**so too, the spiritual life doesn’t last long on a spiritual path where women are allowed to go forth.*";
P_HTM[12711]="*Seyyathāpi, ānanda, sampanne ucchukkhette mañjiṭṭhikā nāma rogajāti nipatati, evaṃ taṃ ucchukkhettaṃ na ciraṭṭhitikaṃ hoti;**Just as a ripe field of sugarcane attacked by red rot won’t last long,*";
P_HTM[12712]="*evameva kho, ānanda, yasmiṃ dhammavinaye labhati mātugāmo agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjaṃ, na taṃ brahmacariyaṃ ciraṭṭhitikaṃ hoti.**so too, the spiritual life doesn’t last long on a spiritual path where women are allowed to go forth.*";
P_HTM[12713]="*Seyyathāpi, ānanda, puriso mahato taḷākassa paṭikacceva āḷiṃ bandheyya yāvadeva udakassa anatikkamanāya;**Just as a man might, as a safeguard, surround a large pool with an embankment, so that the water won’t overflow,*";
P_HTM[12714]="*evameva kho, ānanda, mayā paṭikacceva bhikkhunīnaṃ aṭṭha garudhammā paññattā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyā”ti.**so too, have I, as a safeguard, laid down the eight important principles, not to be breached for life.”*";
P_HTM[12715]="*Bhikkhunīnaṃ aṭṭha garudhammā niṭṭhitā.**The eight important principles for nuns are finished.*";
P_HTM[12716]="*3. Bhikkhunīupasampadānujānana**3. The allowance for the full ordination of nuns*";
P_HTM[12717]="*Atha kho mahāpajāpati gotamī yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi.**Mahāpajāpati went to the Buddha, bowed down,*";
P_HTM[12718]="*Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho mahāpajāpati gotamī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[12719]="*“kathāhaṃ, bhante, imāsu sākiyānīsu paṭipajjāmī”ti?**“Venerable Sir, what should I do with these Sakyan women?”*";
P_HTM[12720]="*Atha kho bhagavā mahāpajāpatiṃ gotamiṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi.**The Buddha then instructed, inspired, and gladdened her with a teaching,*";
P_HTM[12721]="*Atha kho mahāpajāpati gotamī bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**after which she bowed down, circumambulated him with her right side toward him, and left.*";
P_HTM[12722]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a Teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[12723]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūhi bhikkhuniyo upasampādetun”ti.**“I allow you to give the full ordination to nuns.”*";
P_HTM[12724]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo mahāpajāpatiṃ gotamiṃ etadavocuṃ—**Soon afterwards those nuns said to Mahāpajāpati,*";
P_HTM[12725]="*“ayyā anupasampannā, mayañcamhā upasampannā;**“We’re ordained, but you’re not,*";
P_HTM[12726]="*evañhi bhagavatā paññattaṃ bhikkhūhi bhikkhuniyo upasampādetabbā”ti.**for the Buddha has laid down that the monks should give the full ordination to nuns.”*";
P_HTM[12727]="*Atha kho mahāpajāpati gotamī yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi.**Mahāpajāpati then went to Venerable Ānanda, bowed down,*";
P_HTM[12728]="*Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho mahāpajāpati gotamī āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca—**and told him*";
P_HTM[12729]="*“imā maṃ, bhante ānanda, bhikkhuniyo evamāhaṃsu—**what the Sakyan women had said.*";
P_HTM[12730]="*‘ayyā anupasampannā, mayañcamhā upasampannā;* **";
P_HTM[12731]="*evañhi bhagavatā paññattaṃ bhikkhūhi bhikkhuniyo upasampādetabbā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[12732]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Ānanda went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[12733]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and told him*";
P_HTM[12734]="*“mahāpajāpati, bhante, gotamī evamāha—**what Mahāpajāpati had said.*";
P_HTM[12735]="*‘imā maṃ, bhante ānanda, bhikkhuniyo evamāhaṃsu—* **";
P_HTM[12736]="*ayyā anupasampannā, mayañcamhā upasampannā;* **";
P_HTM[12737]="*evañhi bhagavatā paññattaṃ bhikkhūhi bhikkhuniyo upasampādetabbā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[12738]="*“Yadaggena, ānanda, mahāpajāpatiyā gotamiyā aṭṭha garudhammā paṭiggahitā, tadeva sā upasampannā”ti.**The Buddha replied, “Mahāpajāpati was ordained from the time she accepted the eight important principles.”*";
P_HTM[12739]="*Atha kho mahāpajāpati gotamī yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi.**On another occasion Mahāpajāpati went to Venerable Ānanda, bowed down,*";
P_HTM[12740]="*Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho mahāpajāpati gotamī āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[12741]="*“ekāhaṃ, bhante ānanda, bhagavantaṃ varaṃ yācāmi.**“Venerable Ānanda, I wish to ask the Buddha for a favor.*";
P_HTM[12742]="*Sādhu, bhante, bhagavā anujāneyya bhikkhūnañca bhikkhunīnañca yathāvuḍḍhaṃ abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ añjalikammaṃ sāmīcikamman”ti.**It would be good if the Buddha allowed the monks and nuns to bow down to one another according to seniority, and likewise to rise up for one another, raise their joined palms to one another, and do acts of respect toward one another according to seniority.”*";
P_HTM[12743]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Venerable Ānanda went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[12744]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and told the Buddha*";
P_HTM[12745]="*“mahāpajāpati, bhante, gotamī evamāha—**what Mahāpajāpati had said.*";
P_HTM[12746]="*‘ekāhaṃ, bhante ānanda, bhagavantaṃ varaṃ yācāmi.* **";
P_HTM[12747]="*Sādhu, bhante, bhagavā anujāneyya bhikkhūnañca bhikkhunīnañca yathāvuḍḍhaṃ abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ añjalikammaṃ sāmīcikamman’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[12748]="*“Aṭṭhānametaṃ, ānanda, anavakāso, yaṃ tathāgato anujāneyya mātugāmassa abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ añjalikammaṃ sāmīcikammaṃ.**The Buddha replied, “It is impossible, Ānanda, that I would allow bowing down to a woman, and likewise rising up for, raising one’s joined palms to, and doing acts of respect toward a woman.*";
P_HTM[12749]="*Imehi nāma, ānanda, aññatitthiyā durakkhātadhammā mātugāmassa abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ añjalikammaṃ sāmīcikammaṃ na karissanti;**Even the monastics of other religions with their flawed teachings don’t bow down to women, or rise up for them, raise their joined palms to them, or do acts of respect toward them.*";
P_HTM[12750]="*kimaṅgaṃ pana tathāgato anujānissati mātugāmassa abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ añjalikammaṃ sāmīcikamman”ti?**So how then could I allow these things?”*";
P_HTM[12751]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**The Buddha then gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[12752]="*“na, bhikkhave, mātugāmassa abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ añjalikammaṃ sāmīcikammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**“You should not bow down to a woman, or rise up for, raise your joined palms to, or do acts of respect toward a woman.*";
P_HTM[12753]="*Yo kareyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[12754]="*Atha kho mahāpajāpati gotamī yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi.**On another occasion Mahāpajāpati went to the Buddha, bowed down,*";
P_HTM[12755]="*Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho mahāpajāpati gotamī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[12756]="*“yāni tāni, bhante, bhikkhunīnaṃ sikkhāpadāni bhikkhūhi sādhāraṇāni, kathaṃ mayaṃ, bhante, tesu sikkhāpadesu paṭipajjāmā”ti?**“Venerable Sir, how should we practice those training rules that the nuns have in common with the monks?”*";
P_HTM[12757]="*“Yāni tāni, gotami, bhikkhunīnaṃ sikkhāpadāni bhikkhūhi sādhāraṇāni, yathā bhikkhū sikkhanti tathā tesu sikkhāpadesu sikkhathā”ti.**“You should practice them in the same way as the monks do.”*";
P_HTM[12758]="*“Yāni pana tāni, bhante, bhikkhunīnaṃ sikkhāpadāni bhikkhūhi asādhāraṇāni, kathaṃ mayaṃ, bhante, tesu sikkhāpadesu paṭipajjāmā”ti?**“And how should we practice those training rules that the nuns don’t have in common with the monks?”*";
P_HTM[12759]="*“Yāni tāni, gotami, bhikkhunīnaṃ sikkhāpadāni bhikkhūhi asādhāraṇāni, yathāpaññattesu sikkhāpadesu sikkhathā”ti.**“You should practice them as they have been laid down.”*";
P_HTM[12760]="*Atha kho mahāpajāpati gotamī yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi.**On another occasion Mahāpajāpati went to the Buddha, bowed down,*";
P_HTM[12761]="*Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho mahāpajāpati gotamī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[12762]="*“sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā saṅkhittena dhammaṃ desetu, yamahaṃ bhagavato dhammaṃ sutvā ekā vūpakaṭṭhā appamattā ātāpinī pahitattā vihareyyan”ti.**“It would be good, Venerable Sir, if you would give me a teaching in brief. I could then stay by myself, secluded, heedful, energetic, and diligent.”*";
P_HTM[12763]="*“Ye kho tvaṃ, gotami, dhamme jāneyyāsi—**“Those things, Gotami, that you know*";
P_HTM[12764]="*ime dhammā sarāgāya saṃvattanti no virāgāya, saññogāya saṃvattanti no visaññogāya, ācayāya saṃvattanti no apacayāya, mahicchatāya saṃvattanti no appicchatāya, asantuṭṭhiyā saṃvattanti no santuṭṭhiyā, saṅgaṇikāya saṃvattanti no pavivekāya, kosajjāya saṃvattanti no vīriyārambhāya, dubbharatāya saṃvattanti no subharatāya;**lead to passion, not to dispassion; to bondage, not to freedom from bondage; to an increase in things, not to a reduction in things; to great desires, not to fewness of wishes; to discontent, not to contentment; to socializing, not to seclusion; to laziness, not to being energetic; to being difficult to support, not to being easy to support—*";
P_HTM[12765]="*ekaṃsena, gotami, dhāreyyāsi—**you should definitely regard them*";
P_HTM[12766]="*neso dhammo, neso vinayo, netaṃ satthusāsananti.**as not the Teaching, not the training, not the Teacher’s instruction.*";
P_HTM[12767]="*Ye ca kho tvaṃ, gotami, dhamme jāneyyāsi—**But those things that you know*";
P_HTM[12768]="*ime dhammā virāgāya saṃvattanti no sarāgāya, visaññogāya saṃvattanti no saññogāya, apacayāya saṃvattanti no ācayāya, appicchatāya saṃvattanti no mahicchatāya, santuṭṭhiyā saṃvattanti no asantuṭṭhiyā, pavivekāya saṃvattanti no saṅgaṇikāya, vīriyārambhāya saṃvattanti no kosajjāya, subharatāya saṃvattanti no dubbharatāya;**lead to dispassion, not to passion; to freedom from bondage, not to bondage; to a reduction in things, not to an increase in things; to fewness of wishes, not to great desires; to contentment, not to discontent; to seclusion, not to socializing; to being energetic, not to laziness; to being easy to support, not to being difficult to support—*";
P_HTM[12769]="*ekaṃsena, gotami, dhāreyyāsi—**you should definitely regard them*";
P_HTM[12770]="*eso dhammo, eso vinayo, etaṃ satthusāsanan”ti.**as the Teaching, the training, the Teacher’s instruction.”*";
P_HTM[12771]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhunīnaṃ pātimokkhaṃ na uddisīyati.**At that time the Monastic Code was not being recited to the nuns.*";
P_HTM[12772]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. …*";
P_HTM[12773]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhunīnaṃ pātimokkhaṃ uddisitun”ti.**“The Monastic Code should be recited to the nuns.”*";
P_HTM[12774]="*Atha kho bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The nuns thought,*";
P_HTM[12775]="*“kena nu kho bhikkhunīnaṃ pātimokkhaṃ uddisitabban”ti?**“Who should recite the Monastic Code to the nuns?”*";
P_HTM[12776]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12777]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūhi bhikkhunīnaṃ pātimokkhaṃ uddisitun”ti.**“The monks should recite the Monastic Code to the nuns.”*";
P_HTM[12778]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhunīnaṃ pātimokkhaṃ uddisanti.**Soon afterwards the monks went to the nuns’ dwelling place to recite the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[12779]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12780]="*“jāyāyo imā imesaṃ, jāriyo imā imesaṃ, idāni ime imāhi saddhiṃ abhiramissantī”ti.**“They are their wives! They are their mistresses! Now they are going to enjoy themselves together.”*";
P_HTM[12781]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12782]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhūhi bhikkhunīnaṃ pātimokkhaṃ uddisitabbaṃ.**“Monks, you should not recite the Monastic Code to the nuns.*";
P_HTM[12783]="*Yo uddiseyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12784]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhunīhi bhikkhunīnaṃ pātimokkhaṃ uddisitun”ti.**The nuns should recite the Monastic Code to the nuns.”*";
P_HTM[12785]="*Bhikkhuniyo na jānanti—**The nuns did not know*";
P_HTM[12786]="*“evaṃ pātimokkhaṃ uddisitabban”ti.**how to recite it.*";
P_HTM[12787]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12788]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūhi bhikkhunīnaṃ ācikkhituṃ—**“The monks should tell the nuns*";
P_HTM[12789]="*‘evaṃ pātimokkhaṃ uddiseyyāthā’”ti.**how to recite the Monastic Code.”*";
P_HTM[12790]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo āpattiṃ na paṭikaronti.**At that time the nuns did not make amends for their offenses.*";
P_HTM[12791]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12792]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā āpatti na paṭikātabbā.**“A nun should make amends for her offenses.*";
P_HTM[12793]="*Yā na paṭikareyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If she doesn’t, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[12794]="*Bhikkhuniyo na jānanti—**The nuns did not know*";
P_HTM[12795]="*“evaṃ āpatti paṭikātabbā”ti.**how to make amends.*";
P_HTM[12796]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12797]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūhi bhikkhunīnaṃ ācikkhituṃ—**“The monks should tell the nuns*";
P_HTM[12798]="*‘evaṃ āpattiṃ paṭikareyyāthā’”ti.**how to make amends for an offense.”*";
P_HTM[12799]="*Atha kho bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The monks thought,*";
P_HTM[12800]="*“kena nu kho bhikkhunīnaṃ āpatti paṭiggahetabbā”ti?**“Who should receive confessions from the nuns?”*";
P_HTM[12801]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12802]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūhi bhikkhunīnaṃ āpattiṃ paṭiggahetun”ti.**“The monks should receive the confession of offenses from the nuns.”*";
P_HTM[12803]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo rathikāyapi byūhepi siṅghāṭakepi bhikkhuṃ passitvā pattaṃ bhūmiyaṃ nikkhipitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā āpattiṃ paṭikaronti.**Soon afterwards, when the nuns saw a monk on a street, in a cul-de-sac, or at an intersection, they would put down their bowl, put their upper robe over one shoulder, squat on their heels, raise their joined palms, and make amends for their offenses.*";
P_HTM[12804]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12805]="*“jāyāyo imā imesaṃ, jāriyo imā imesaṃ, rattiṃ vimānetvā idāni khamāpentī”ti.**“They are their wives! They are their mistresses! Having offended them at night, they now ask for forgiveness.”*";
P_HTM[12806]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12807]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhūhi bhikkhunīnaṃ āpatti paṭiggahetabbā.**“Monks, you should not receive confessions from the nuns.*";
P_HTM[12808]="*Yo paṭiggaṇheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12809]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhunīhi bhikkhunīnaṃ āpattiṃ paṭiggahetun”ti.**The nuns should receive the confession of offenses from the nuns.”*";
P_HTM[12810]="*Bhikkhuniyo na jānanti—**The nuns did not know*";
P_HTM[12811]="*“evaṃ āpatti paṭiggahetabbā”ti.**how to receive confessions.*";
P_HTM[12812]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12813]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūhi bhikkhunīnaṃ ācikkhituṃ—**“The monks should tell the nuns*";
P_HTM[12814]="*‘evaṃ āpattiṃ paṭiggaṇheyyāthā’”ti.**how to receive offenses.”*";
P_HTM[12815]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhunīnaṃ kammaṃ na kariyati.**At that time the nuns’ legal procedures were not being done.*";
P_HTM[12816]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12817]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhunīnaṃ kammaṃ kātun”ti.**“Monks, I allow the doing of legal procedures for the nuns.”*";
P_HTM[12818]="*Atha kho bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The monks thought,*";
P_HTM[12819]="*“kena nu kho bhikkhunīnaṃ kammaṃ kātabban”ti?**“Who should do the nuns’ procedures?”*";
P_HTM[12820]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12821]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūhi bhikkhunīnaṃ kammaṃ kātun”ti.**“The monks should do the nuns’ procedures.”*";
P_HTM[12822]="*Tena kho pana samayena katakammā bhikkhuniyo rathikāyapi byūhepi siṅghāṭakepi bhikkhuṃ passitvā pattaṃ bhūmiyaṃ nikkhipitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā khamāpenti “evaṃ nūna kātabban”ti maññamānā.**Soon afterwards, when nuns who had had a legal procedure done against them saw a monk on a street, in a cul-de-sac, or at an intersection, they would put down their bowl, put their upper robe over one shoulder, squat on their heels, raise their joined palms, and ask for forgiveness, thinking, “This is the way to do it.”*";
P_HTM[12823]="*Manussā tatheva ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12824]="*“jāyāyo imā imesaṃ, jāriyo imā imesaṃ, rattiṃ vimānetvā idāni khamāpentī”ti.**“They are their wives! They are their mistresses! Having offended them at night, they now ask for forgiveness.”*";
P_HTM[12825]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12826]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhūhi bhikkhunīnaṃ kammaṃ kātabbaṃ.**“Monks, you should not do the nuns’ legal procedures.*";
P_HTM[12827]="*Yo kareyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12828]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhunīhi bhikkhunīnaṃ kammaṃ kātun”ti.**The nuns should do the nuns’ legal procedures.”*";
P_HTM[12829]="*Bhikkhuniyo na jānanti—**The nuns did not know*";
P_HTM[12830]="*“evaṃ kammaṃ kātabban”ti.**how to do procedures.*";
P_HTM[12831]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12832]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūhi bhikkhunīnaṃ ācikkhituṃ—**“The monks should tell the nuns*";
P_HTM[12833]="*‘evaṃ kammaṃ kareyyāthā’”ti.**how to do legal procedures.”*";
P_HTM[12834]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo saṅghamajjhe bhaṇḍanajātā kalahajātā vivādāpannā aññamaññaṃ mukhasattīhi vitudantā viharanti.**On one occasion the nuns were arguing and disputing in the midst of the Sangha, attacking one another verbally,*";
P_HTM[12835]="*Na sakkonti taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**and they were not able to resolve that legal issue.*";
P_HTM[12836]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12837]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūhi bhikkhunīnaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametun”ti.**“I allow the monks to resolve the nuns’ legal issues.”*";
P_HTM[12838]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū bhikkhunīnaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasamenti.**Soon afterwards the monks were resolving a legal issue for the nuns.*";
P_HTM[12839]="*Tasmiṃ kho pana adhikaraṇe vinicchiyamāne dissanti bhikkhuniyo kammappattāyopi āpattigāminiyopi.**While they were deliberating on the issue, there were nuns who needed a legal procedure to be done and who were guilty of an offense*";
P_HTM[12840]="*Bhikkhuniyo evamāhaṃsu—**The nuns said,*";
P_HTM[12841]="*“sādhu, bhante, ayyāva bhikkhunīnaṃ kammaṃ karontu, ayyāva bhikkhunīnaṃ āpattiṃ paṭiggaṇhantu;**“It would be good, Venerables, if you would do the procedure for the nuns and receive their confession of offenses,*";
P_HTM[12842]="*evañhi bhagavatā paññattaṃ bhikkhūhi bhikkhunīnaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametabban”ti.**for the Buddha has laid down that the nuns’ legal issues should be resolved by the monks.”*";
P_HTM[12843]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12844]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūhi bhikkhunīnaṃ kammaṃ āropetvā bhikkhunīnaṃ niyyādetuṃ—**“Monks, I allow you to determine the nature of the nuns’ legal procedure, before handing over to the nuns for them to do it.*";
P_HTM[12845]="*bhikkhunīhi bhikkhunīnaṃ kammaṃ kātuṃ, bhikkhūhi bhikkhunīnaṃ āpattiṃ āropetvā bhikkhunīnaṃ niyyādetuṃ, bhikkhunīhi bhikkhunīnaṃ āpattiṃ paṭiggahetun”ti.**And I allow you to charge a nun with an offense, before handing over to the nuns for them to receive the confession.”*";
P_HTM[12846]="*Tena kho pana samayena uppalavaṇṇāya bhikkhuniyā antevāsinī bhikkhunī satta vassāni bhagavantaṃ anubandhā hoti vinayaṃ pariyāpuṇantī.**At that time a nun who was a pupil of the nun Uppalavaṇṇā had followed the Buddha around for seven years to learn the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[12847]="*Tassā muṭṭhassatiniyā gahito gahito mussati.**But because of her absentmindedness, she repeatedly forgot what she had learned.*";
P_HTM[12848]="*Assosi kho sā bhikkhunī—**When she heard*";
P_HTM[12849]="*“bhagavā kira sāvatthiṃ gantukāmo”ti.**that the Buddha wanted to go to Sāvatthī,*";
P_HTM[12850]="*Atha kho tassā bhikkhuniyā etadahosi—**she reflected*";
P_HTM[12851]="*“ahaṃ kho satta vassāni bhagavantaṃ anubandhiṃ vinayaṃ pariyāpuṇantī.* **";
P_HTM[12852]="*Tassā me muṭṭhassatiniyā gahito gahito mussati.**on her absentmindedness and thought,*";
P_HTM[12853]="*Dukkaraṃ kho pana mātugāmena yāvajīvaṃ satthāraṃ anubandhituṃ.**“It’s hard for a woman to follow the Teacher around all her life.*";
P_HTM[12854]="*Kathaṃ nu kho mayā paṭipajjitabban”ti?**So what should I do?”*";
P_HTM[12855]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**She told the nuns what she had thought,*";
P_HTM[12856]="*Bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**who in turn told the monks,*";
P_HTM[12857]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**who then told the Buddha. The Buddha said,*";
P_HTM[12858]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūhi bhikkhunīnaṃ vinayaṃ vācetun”ti.**“I allow the monks to teach the Monastic Law to the nuns.”*";
P_HTM[12859]="*Paṭhamabhāṇavāro niṭṭhito.**The first section for recitation is finished.*";
P_HTM[12860]="*Atha kho bhagavā vesāliyaṃ yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena sāvatthi tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**When the Buddha had stayed at Vesālī for as long as he liked, he set out wandering toward Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[12861]="*Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena sāvatthi tadavasari.**When he eventually arrived,*";
P_HTM[12862]="*Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**he stayed in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[12863]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo kaddamodakena osiñcanti—**At that time the monks from the group of six tried to attract the nuns by splashing them with muddy water.*";
P_HTM[12864]="*appeva nāma amhesu sārajjeyyunti.* **";
P_HTM[12865]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12866]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā bhikkhuniyo kaddamodakena osiñcitabbā.**“Monks, you should not splash the nuns with muddy water.*";
P_HTM[12867]="*Yo osiñceyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12868]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tassa bhikkhuno daṇḍakammaṃ kātun”ti.**I allow the nuns to penalize a monk who acts like this.”*";
P_HTM[12869]="*Atha kho bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The monks thought,*";
P_HTM[12870]="*“kiṃ nu kho daṇḍakammaṃ kātabban”ti?**“What sort of penalty should they impose?”*";
P_HTM[12871]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12872]="*“Avandiyo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bhikkhunisaṅghena kātabbo”ti.**“The Sangha of nuns should not pay respect to such a monk.”*";
P_HTM[12873]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kāyaṃ vivaritvā bhikkhunīnaṃ dassenti …pe…**Soon afterwards the monks from the group of six tried to attract the nuns by exposing their bodies to them,*";
P_HTM[12874]="*ūruṃ vivaritvā bhikkhunīnaṃ dassenti, aṅgajātaṃ vivaritvā bhikkhunīnaṃ dassenti, bhikkhuniyo obhāsenti, bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ sampayojenti—**by exposing their thighs to them, and by exposing their genitals to them. And they spoke indecently to the nuns and associated inappropriately with them.*";
P_HTM[12875]="*appeva nāma amhesu sārajjeyyunti.* **";
P_HTM[12876]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12877]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā kāyo vivaritvā bhikkhunīnaṃ dassetabbo, na ūru vivaritvā bhikkhunīnaṃ dassetabbo, na aṅgajātaṃ vivaritvā bhikkhunīnaṃ dassetabbaṃ, na bhikkhuniyo obhāsitabbā, na bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ sampayojetabbaṃ.**“Monks, you should not expose your body to the nuns; you should not expose your thighs to the nuns; you should not expose your genitals to the nuns; you should not speak indecently to the nuns; and you should not associate inappropriately with the nuns.*";
P_HTM[12878]="*Yo sampayojeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you associate inappropriately with the nuns, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12879]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tassa bhikkhuno daṇḍakammaṃ kātun”ti.**I allow the nuns to penalize a monk who acts like this.”*";
P_HTM[12880]="*Atha kho bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The monks thought,*";
P_HTM[12881]="*“kiṃ nu kho daṇḍakammaṃ kātabban”ti?**“What sort of penalty can they impose?”*";
P_HTM[12882]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12883]="*“Avandiyo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bhikkhunisaṅghena kātabbo”ti.**“The Sangha of nuns should not pay respect to such a monk.”*";
P_HTM[12884]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhuṃ kaddamodakena osiñcanti—**Soon afterwards the nuns from the group of six tried to attract a monk by splashing him with muddy water.*";
P_HTM[12885]="*appeva nāma amhesu sārajjeyyunti.* **";
P_HTM[12886]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12887]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā bhikkhu kaddamodakena osiñcitabbo.**“A nun should not splash a monk with muddy water.*";
P_HTM[12888]="*Yā osiñceyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12889]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tassā bhikkhuniyā daṇḍakammaṃ kātun”ti.**I allow you to penalize such a nun.”*";
P_HTM[12890]="*Atha kho bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The monks thought,*";
P_HTM[12891]="*“kiṃ nu kho daṇḍakammaṃ kātabban”ti?**“What sort of penalty can we impose?”*";
P_HTM[12892]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12893]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, āvaraṇaṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to place restrictions on her.”*";
P_HTM[12894]="*Āvaraṇe kate na ādiyanti.**She did not adhere to the restrictions.*";
P_HTM[12895]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12896]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ovādaṃ ṭhapetun”ti.**“I allow you cancel the half-monthly instruction.”*";
P_HTM[12897]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo kāyaṃ vivaritvā bhikkhūnaṃ dassenti, thanaṃ vivaritvā bhikkhūnaṃ dassenti, ūruṃ vivaritvā bhikkhūnaṃ dassenti, aṅgajātaṃ vivaritvā bhikkhūnaṃ dassenti, bhikkhū obhāsenti, bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ sampayojenti—**At that time the nuns from the group of six tried to attract the monks by exposing their bodies to them, by exposing their breasts to them, by exposing their thighs to them, and by exposing their genitals to them. And they spoke indecently to the monks and associated inappropriately with them.*";
P_HTM[12898]="*appeva nāma amhesu sārajjeyyunti.* **";
P_HTM[12899]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12900]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā kāyo vivaritvā bhikkhūnaṃ dassetabbo …pe…**“A nun should not expose her body to the monks;*";
P_HTM[12901]="*na thano vivaritvā bhikkhūnaṃ dassetabbo, na ūru vivaritvā bhikkhūnaṃ dassetabbo, na aṅgajātaṃ vivaritvā bhikkhūnaṃ dassetabbaṃ, na bhikkhū obhāsitabbā, na bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ sampayojetabbaṃ.**she should not expose her breasts to the monks; she should not expose her thighs to the monks; she should not expose her genitals to the monks; she should not speak indecently to the monks; and she should not associate inappropriately with the monks.*";
P_HTM[12902]="*Yā sampayojeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she associates inappropriately with the monks, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12903]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tassā bhikkhuniyā daṇḍakammaṃ kātun”ti.**I allow the monks to penalize such a nun.”*";
P_HTM[12904]="*Atha kho bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The monks thought,*";
P_HTM[12905]="*“kiṃ nu kho daṇḍakammaṃ kātabban”ti?**“What sort of penalty can we impose?”*";
P_HTM[12906]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12907]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, āvaraṇaṃ kātun”ti.**“I allow you to place restrictions on her.”*";
P_HTM[12908]="*Āvaraṇe kate na ādiyanti.**She did not adhere to the restrictions.*";
P_HTM[12909]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12910]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ovādaṃ ṭhapetun”ti.**“I allow you cancel the half-monthly instruction.”*";
P_HTM[12911]="*Atha kho bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The monks thought,*";
P_HTM[12912]="*“kappati nu kho ovādaṭṭhapitāya bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ uposathaṃ kātuṃ, na nu kho kappatī”ti?**“Is it allowable or not to do the observance-day procedure with a nun whose half-monthly instruction has been canceled?”*";
P_HTM[12913]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12914]="*“Na, bhikkhave, ovādaṭṭhapitāya bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ uposatho kātabbo, yāva na taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasantaṃ hotī”ti.**“Until that legal issue has been settled it’s not allowable to do the observance-day procedure with a nun whose half-monthly instruction has been canceled.”*";
P_HTM[12915]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā udāyī ovādaṃ ṭhapetvā cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**On one occasion Venerable Udāyī canceled the half-monthly instruction and then set out wandering.*";
P_HTM[12916]="*Bhikkhuniyo ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[12917]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyo udāyī ovādaṃ ṭhapetvā cārikaṃ pakkamissatī”ti.**“How could Venerable Udāyī do this?”*";
P_HTM[12918]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12919]="*“Na, bhikkhave, ovādaṃ ṭhapetvā cārikā pakkamitabbā.**“Monks, you should not cancel the half-monthly instruction and then set out wandering.*";
P_HTM[12920]="*Yo pakkameyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[12921]="*Tena kho pana samayena bālā abyattā ovādaṃ ṭhapenti.**At that time even the monks who were ignorant and incompetent canceled the half-monthly instruction.*";
P_HTM[12922]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12923]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bālena abyattena ovādo ṭhapetabbo.**“A monk who is ignorant and incompetent should not cancel the half-monthly instruction.*";
P_HTM[12924]="*Yo ṭhapeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If he does, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[12925]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū avatthusmiṃ akāraṇe ovādaṃ ṭhapenti.**At that time the monks canceled the half-monthly instruction without reason.*";
P_HTM[12926]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12927]="*“Na, bhikkhave, avatthusmiṃ akāraṇe ovādo ṭhapetabbo.**“A monk should not cancel the half-monthly instruction without reason.*";
P_HTM[12928]="*Yo ṭhapeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If he does, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[12929]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū ovādaṃ ṭhapetvā vinicchayaṃ na denti.**At that time the monks did not deliberate after canceling the half-monthly instruction.*";
P_HTM[12930]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12931]="*“Na, bhikkhave, ovādaṃ ṭhapetvā vinicchayo na dātabbo.**“You should deliberate after canceling the half-monthly instruction.*";
P_HTM[12932]="*Yo na dadeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you don’t, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[12933]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo ovādaṃ na gacchanti.**At that time the nuns did not go to the half-monthly instruction.*";
P_HTM[12934]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12935]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā ovādo na gantabbo.**“A nun should go to the half-monthly instruction.*";
P_HTM[12936]="*Yā na gaccheyya, yathādhammo kāretabbo”ti.**If she doesn’t, she should be dealt with according to the rule.*";
P_HTM[12937]="*Tena kho pana samayena sabbo bhikkhunisaṅgho ovādaṃ gacchati.**At that time the entire Sangha of nuns went to the half-monthly instruction.*";
P_HTM[12938]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12939]="*“jāyāyo imā imesaṃ, jāriyo imā imesaṃ, idāni ime imāhi saddhiṃ abhiramissantī”ti.**“They are their wives! They are their mistresses! Now they are going to enjoy themselves together.”*";
P_HTM[12940]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12941]="*“Na, bhikkhave, sabbena bhikkhunisaṅghena ovādo gantabbo.**“The whole sangha of nuns should not go to the half-monthly instruction.*";
P_HTM[12942]="*Gaccheyya ce, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it does, there is an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12943]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, catūhi pañcahi bhikkhunīhi ovādaṃ gantun”ti.**Four or five nuns should go to the instruction.”*";
P_HTM[12944]="*Tena kho pana samayena catasso pañca bhikkhuniyo ovādaṃ gacchanti.**Soon afterwards four or five nuns went to the half-monthly instruction.*";
P_HTM[12945]="*Manussā tatheva ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12946]="*“jāyāyo imā imesaṃ, jāriyo imā imesaṃ, idāni ime imāhi saddhiṃ abhiramissantī”ti.**“They are their wives! They are their mistresses! Now they are going to enjoy themselves together.”*";
P_HTM[12947]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12948]="*“Na, bhikkhave, catūhi pañcahi bhikkhunīhi ovādo gantabbo.**“Four or five nuns should not go to the half-monthly instruction.*";
P_HTM[12949]="*Gaccheyyuñce, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If they do, there is an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12950]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, dve tisso bhikkhuniyo ovādaṃ gantuṃ.**Two or three nuns should go to the instruction.*";
P_HTM[12951]="*Ekaṃ bhikkhuṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**They should go to a monk, put their upper robe over one shoulder, bow down at his feet, squat on their heels, raise their joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[12952]="*‘bhikkhunisaṅgho, ayya, bhikkhusaṅghassa pāde vandati, ovādūpasaṅkamanañca yācati;**‘Venerable, the Sangha of nuns bows down at the feet of the Sangha of monks and asks to come for the half-monthly instruction.*";
P_HTM[12953]="*labhatu kira, ayya, bhikkhunisaṅgho ovādūpasaṅkamanan’ti.**Please allow the Sangha of nuns to come for the instruction.’*";
P_HTM[12954]="*Tena bhikkhunā pātimokkhuddesako upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo—**That monk should go to the reciter of the Monastic Code and tell him*";
P_HTM[12955]="*‘bhikkhunisaṅgho, bhante, bhikkhusaṅghassa pāde vandati, ovādūpasaṅkamanañca yācati;**of the nuns’ request.*";
P_HTM[12956]="*labhatu kira, bhante, bhikkhunisaṅgho ovādūpasaṅkamanan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[12957]="*Pātimokkhuddesakena vattabbo—**The reciter should say,*";
P_HTM[12958]="*‘atthi koci bhikkhu bhikkhunovādako sammato’ti?**‘Is there anyone who has been appointed as instructor of the nuns?’*";
P_HTM[12959]="*Sace hoti koci bhikkhu bhikkhunovādako sammato, pātimokkhuddesakena vattabbo—**If there is, the reciter should say,*";
P_HTM[12960]="*‘itthannāmo bhikkhu bhikkhunovādako sammato, taṃ bhikkhunisaṅgho upasaṅkamatū’ti.**‘Monk so-and-so has been appointed. The Sangha of nuns should approach him.’*";
P_HTM[12961]="*Sace na hoti koci bhikkhu bhikkhunovādako sammato, pātimokkhuddesakena vattabbo—**If there isn’t, the reciter should say,*";
P_HTM[12962]="*‘ko āyasmā ussahati bhikkhuniyo ovaditun’ti?**‘Who is able to instruct the nuns?’*";
P_HTM[12963]="*Sace koci ussahati bhikkhuniyo ovadituṃ, so ca hoti aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgato, sammannitvā vattabbo—**If there is someone who is able and who has the eight required qualities, he should be appointed. The reciter should then say,*";
P_HTM[12964]="*‘itthannāmo bhikkhu bhikkhunovādako sammato, taṃ bhikkhunisaṅgho upasaṅkamatū’ti.**‘Monk so-and-so has been appointed. The Sangha of nuns should approach him.’*";
P_HTM[12965]="*Sace na koci ussahati bhikkhuniyo ovadituṃ, pātimokkhuddesakena vattabbo—**If no one is able to instruct the nuns, the reciter of the Monastic Code should say,*";
P_HTM[12966]="*‘natthi koci bhikkhu bhikkhunovādako sammato, pāsādikena bhikkhunisaṅgho sampādetū’”ti.**‘No monk has been appointed as instructor of the nuns. The Sangha of nuns should carry on with serenity.’”*";
P_HTM[12967]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū ovādaṃ na gaṇhanti.**On one occasion the monks did not agree to give the half-monthly instruction.*";
P_HTM[12968]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12969]="*“Na, bhikkhave, ovādo na gahetabbo.**“You should agree to give the half-monthly instruction.*";
P_HTM[12970]="*Yo na gaṇheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you don’t, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[12971]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu bālo hoti.**On one occasion the nuns went to a monk who was ignorant*";
P_HTM[12972]="*Taṃ bhikkhuniyo upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ—**and said,*";
P_HTM[12973]="*“ovādaṃ, ayya, gaṇhāhī”ti.**“Venerable, please agree to give the half-monthly instruction.”*";
P_HTM[12974]="*“Ahañhi, bhaginī, bālo;**“But I’m ignorant, sisters.*";
P_HTM[12975]="*kathāhaṃ ovādaṃ gaṇhāmī”ti?**How can I agree to give the instruction?”*";
P_HTM[12976]="*“Gaṇhāhayya, ovādaṃ;**“Please agree to give the instruction,*";
P_HTM[12977]="*evañhi bhagavatā paññattaṃ—**for the Buddha has laid down*";
P_HTM[12978]="*bhikkhūhi bhikkhunīnaṃ ovādo gahetabbo”ti.**that a monk should agree to give the instruction to the nuns.”*";
P_HTM[12979]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12980]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ṭhapetvā bālaṃ, avasesehi ovādaṃ gahetun”ti.**“Except if you are ignorant, you should agree to give the half-monthly instruction.”*";
P_HTM[12981]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu gilāno hoti.**On one occasion the nuns went to a monk who was sick*";
P_HTM[12982]="*Taṃ bhikkhuniyo upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ—**and said,*";
P_HTM[12983]="*“ovādaṃ, ayya, gaṇhāhī”ti.**“Venerable, please agree to give the half-monthly instruction.”*";
P_HTM[12984]="*“Ahañhi, bhaginī, gilāno;**“But I’m sick, sisters.*";
P_HTM[12985]="*kathāhaṃ ovādaṃ gaṇhāmī”ti?**How can I agree to give the instruction?”*";
P_HTM[12986]="*“Gaṇhāhayya, ovādaṃ;**“Please agree to give the instruction,*";
P_HTM[12987]="*evañhi bhagavatā paññattaṃ—**for the Buddha has laid down*";
P_HTM[12988]="*ṭhapetvā bālaṃ, avasesehi ovādo gahetabbo”ti.**that a monk should agree to give the instruction to the nuns, except if he is ignorant.”*";
P_HTM[12989]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12990]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ṭhapetvā bālaṃ, ṭhapetvā gilānaṃ, avasesehi ovādaṃ gahetun”ti.**“Except if you are ignorant or sick, you should agree to give the half-monthly instruction.”*";
P_HTM[12991]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu gamiko hoti.**On one occasion the nuns went to a monk who was about to depart*";
P_HTM[12992]="*Taṃ bhikkhuniyo upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ—**and said,*";
P_HTM[12993]="*“ovādaṃ, ayya, gaṇhāhī”ti.**“Venerable, please agree to give the half-monthly instruction.”*";
P_HTM[12994]="*“Ahañhi, bhaginī, gamiko;**“But I’m about to depart, sisters.*";
P_HTM[12995]="*kathāhaṃ ovādaṃ gaṇhāmī”ti?**How can I agree to give the instruction?”*";
P_HTM[12996]="*“Gaṇhāhayya, ovādaṃ;**“Please agree to give the instruction,*";
P_HTM[12997]="*evañhi bhagavatā paññattaṃ—**for the Buddha has laid down*";
P_HTM[12998]="*ṭhapetvā bālaṃ, ṭhapetvā gilānaṃ, avasesehi ovādo gahetabbo”ti.**that a monk should agree to give the instruction to the nuns, except if he is ignorant or sick.”*";
P_HTM[12999]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13000]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ṭhapetvā bālaṃ, ṭhapetvā gilānaṃ, ṭhapetvā gamikaṃ, avasesehi ovādaṃ gahetun”ti.**“Except if you are ignorant, sick, or about to depart, you should agree to give the half-monthly instruction.”*";
P_HTM[13001]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu araññe viharati.**On one occasion the nuns went to a monk who was staying in the wilderness*";
P_HTM[13002]="*Taṃ bhikkhuniyo upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ—**and said,*";
P_HTM[13003]="*“ovādaṃ, ayya, gaṇhāhī”ti.**“Venerable, please agree to give the half-monthly instruction.”*";
P_HTM[13004]="*“Ahañhi, bhaginī, araññe viharāmi;**“But I’m staying in the wilderness, sisters.*";
P_HTM[13005]="*kathāhaṃ ovādaṃ gaṇhāmī”ti?**How can I agree to give the instruction?”*";
P_HTM[13006]="*“Gaṇhāhayya, ovādaṃ;**“Please agree to give the instruction,*";
P_HTM[13007]="*evañhi bhagavatā paññattaṃ—**for the Buddha has laid down*";
P_HTM[13008]="*ṭhapetvā bālaṃ, ṭhapetvā gilānaṃ, ṭhapetvā gamikaṃ, avasesehi ovādo gahetabbo”ti.**that a monk should agree to give the instruction to the nuns, except if he is ignorant, sick, or about to depart.”*";
P_HTM[13009]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13010]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, āraññikena bhikkhunā ovādaṃ gahetuṃ, saṅketañca kātuṃ—**“If you are staying in the wilderness, you should agree to give the half-monthly instruction. You should make an appointment, saying,*";
P_HTM[13011]="*atra patiharissāmī”ti.**‘I’ll return here.’”*";
P_HTM[13012]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū ovādaṃ gahetvā na ārocenti.**At that time the monks agreed to give the half-monthly instruction without telling the reciter of the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[13013]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13014]="*“Na, bhikkhave, ovādo na ārocetabbo.**“When you have agreed to give the half-monthly instruction, you should inform the reciter of the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[13015]="*Yo na āroceyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you don’t, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[13016]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū ovādaṃ gahetvā na paccāharanti.**At that time the monks who had agreed to give the half-monthly instruction did not return to give it.*";
P_HTM[13017]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13018]="*“Na, bhikkhave, ovādo na paccāharitabbo.**“You should return to give the half-monthly instruction.*";
P_HTM[13019]="*Yo na paccāhareyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you don’t, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[13020]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo saṅketaṃ na gacchanti.**On one occasion the nuns did not go to the appointment.*";
P_HTM[13021]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13022]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā saṅketaṃ na gantabbaṃ.**“A nun should go to the appointment.*";
P_HTM[13023]="*Yā na gaccheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If she doesn’t, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[13024]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo dīghāni kāyabandhanāni dhārenti, teheva phāsukā nāmenti.**The nuns wore long belts that they fixed into ribs.*";
P_HTM[13025]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti …pe…**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13026]="*seyyathāpi gihinī kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[13027]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13028]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā dīghaṃ kāyabandhanaṃ dhāretabbaṃ.**“A nun should not wear a long belt.*";
P_HTM[13029]="*Yā dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13030]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā ekapariyākataṃ kāyabandhanaṃ, na ca tena phāsukā nāmetabbā.**I allow a nun to wear a belt that goes once around the body, and she should not fix it into ribs.*";
P_HTM[13031]="*Yā nāmeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[13032]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo vilīvena paṭṭena phāsukā nāmenti …pe…**The nuns fixed strips of split bamboo into ribs,*";
P_HTM[13033]="*cammapaṭṭena phāsukā nāmenti.**strips of leather into ribs,*";
P_HTM[13034]="*Dussapaṭṭena phāsukā nāmenti.**strips of fabric into ribs,*";
P_HTM[13035]="*Dussaveṇiyā phāsukā nāmenti.**interlaced fabric into ribs,*";
P_HTM[13036]="*Dussavaṭṭiyā phāsukā nāmenti.**rolled-up fabric into ribs,*";
P_HTM[13037]="*Coḷapaṭṭena phāsukā nāmenti.**strips of cloth into ribs,*";
P_HTM[13038]="*Coḷaveṇiyā phāsukā nāmenti.**interlaced cloth into ribs,*";
P_HTM[13039]="*Coḷavaṭṭiyā phāsukā nāmenti.**rolled-up cloth into ribs,*";
P_HTM[13040]="*Suttaveṇiyā phāsukā nāmenti.**interlaced strings into ribs,*";
P_HTM[13041]="*Suttavaṭṭiyā phāsukā nāmenti.**and rolled-up strings into ribs.*";
P_HTM[13042]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti …pe…**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13043]="*seyyathāpi gihinī kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[13044]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13045]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā vilīvena paṭṭena phāsukā nāmetabbā …pe…**“A nun should not fix strips of split bamboo, strips of leather, strips of fabric, interlaced fabric, rolled-up fabric, strips of cloth, interlaced cloth, rolled-up cloth, interlaced strings,*";
P_HTM[13046]="*na suttavaṭṭiyā phāsukā nāmetabbā.**or rolled-up strings into ribs.*";
P_HTM[13047]="*Yā nāmeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[13048]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo aṭṭhillena jaghanaṃ ghaṃsāpenti …pe…**The nuns had their loins rubbed with bones,*";
P_HTM[13049]="*gohanukena jaghanaṃ koṭṭāpenti, hatthaṃ koṭṭāpenti, hatthakocchaṃ koṭṭāpenti, pādaṃ koṭṭāpenti, pādakocchaṃ koṭṭāpenti, ūruṃ koṭṭāpenti, mukhaṃ koṭṭāpenti, dantamaṃsaṃ koṭṭāpenti.**their loins tapped with a cow’s jaw bone, their palms tapped, the back of their hands tapped, the soles of their feet tapped, the top of their feet tapped, their thighs tapped, their faces tapped, and their gums tapped with a cow’s jaw bone.*";
P_HTM[13050]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti …pe…**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13051]="*seyyathāpi gihinī kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[13052]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13053]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā aṭṭhillena jaghanaṃ ghaṃsāpetabbaṃ …pe…**“A nun should not have her loins rubbed with bones, her loins tapped with a cow’s jaw bone, her palms tapped, the back of her hands tapped, the soles of her feet tapped, the top of her feet tapped, her thighs tapped, her face tapped,*";
P_HTM[13054]="*na dantamaṃsaṃ koṭṭāpetabbaṃ.**or her gums tapped with a cow’s jaw bone.*";
P_HTM[13055]="*Yā koṭṭāpeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[13056]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo mukhaṃ ālimpanti …pe…**The nuns from the group of six used facial ointments,*";
P_HTM[13057]="*mukhaṃ ummaddenti, mukhaṃ cuṇṇenti, manosilikāya mukhaṃ lañchenti, aṅgarāgaṃ karonti, mukharāgaṃ karonti, aṅgarāgamukharāgaṃ karonti.**applied creams, powdered their face, applied rouge to their face, wore cosmetics on their body, wore cosmetics on their face, and wore cosmetics on their body and face.*";
P_HTM[13058]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti …pe…**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13059]="*seyyathāpi gihinī kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[13060]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13061]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā mukhaṃ ālimpitabbaṃ …pe…**“A nun should not use facial ointments,*";
P_HTM[13062]="*na mukhaṃ ummadditabbaṃ, na mukhaṃ cuṇṇetabbaṃ, na manosilikāya mukhaṃ lañchetabbaṃ, na aṅgarāgo kātabbo, na mukharāgo kātabbo, na aṅgarāgamukharāgo kātabbo.**apply creams, powder her face, apply rouge to her face, wear cosmetics on her body, wear cosmetics on her face, or wear cosmetics on her body and face.*";
P_HTM[13063]="*Yā kareyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[13064]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo avaṅgaṃ karonti …pe…**The nuns from the group of six made up their eyes,*";
P_HTM[13065]="*visesakaṃ karonti, olokanakena olokenti, sāloke tiṭṭhanti;**painted dots on their forehead, stared out the windows, exposed themselves to view,*";
P_HTM[13066]="*naccaṃ kārāpenti, vesiṃ vuṭṭhāpenti, pānāgāraṃ ṭhapenti, sūnaṃ ṭhapenti, āpaṇaṃ pasārenti, vaḍḍhiṃ payojenti, vaṇijjaṃ payojenti, dāsaṃ upaṭṭhāpenti, dāsiṃ upaṭṭhāpenti, kammakāraṃ upaṭṭhāpenti, kammakāriṃ upaṭṭhāpenti, tiracchānagataṃ upaṭṭhāpenti, harītakapakkikaṃ pakiṇanti, namatakaṃ dhārenti.**organized dancing, organized sex workers, set up bars, set up slaughterhouses, set up shops, made loans, engaged in trade, were attended on by slaves, were attended on by servants, were attended on by animals, traded in raw and cooked greens, and wore felt.*";
P_HTM[13067]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti …pe…**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13068]="*seyyathāpi gihinī kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[13069]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13070]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā avaṅgaṃ kātabbaṃ …pe…**“A nun should not make up her eyes,*";
P_HTM[13071]="*na visesakaṃ kātabbaṃ, na olokanakena oloketabbaṃ, na sāloke ṭhātabbaṃ, na naccaṃ kārāpetabbaṃ, na vesī vuṭṭhāpetabbā, na pānāgāraṃ ṭhapetabbaṃ, na sūnā ṭhapetabbā, na āpaṇo pasāretabbo, na vaḍḍhi payojetabbā, na vaṇijjā payojetabbā, na dāso upaṭṭhāpetabbo, na dāsī upaṭṭhāpetabbā, na kammakāro upaṭṭhāpetabbo, na kammakārī upaṭṭhāpetabbā, na tiracchānagato upaṭṭhāpetabbo, na harītakapakkikaṃ pakiṇitabbaṃ, na namatakaṃ dhāretabbaṃ.**paint dots on her forehead, stare out the windows, expose herself to view, organize dancing, organize sex workers, set up bars, set up slaughterhouses, set up shops, make loans, engage in trade, be attended on by slaves, be attended on by servants, be attended on by animals, trade in raw and cooked greens, or wear felt.*";
P_HTM[13072]="*Yā dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[13073]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo sabbanīlakāni cīvarāni dhārenti …pe…**The nuns from the group of six wore entirely blue robes,*";
P_HTM[13074]="*sabbapītakāni cīvarāni dhārenti, sabbalohitakāni cīvarāni dhārenti, sabbamañjiṭṭhikāni cīvarāni dhārenti, sabbakaṇhāni cīvarāni dhārenti, sabbamahāraṅgarattāni cīvarāni dhārenti, sabbamahānāmarattāni cīvarāni dhārenti, acchinnadasāni cīvarāni dhārenti, dīghadasāni cīvarāni dhārenti, pupphadasāni cīvarāni dhārenti, phaladasāni cīvarāni dhārenti, kañcukaṃ dhārenti, tirīṭakaṃ dhārenti.**entirely yellow robes, entirely red robes, entirely magenta robes, entirely black robes, entirely orange robes, entirely beige robes, robes with borders made from a single piece of cloth, robes with long borders, robes with floral borders, robes with borders decorated with snakes’ hoods, close-fitting jackets, and lodh tree robes.*";
P_HTM[13075]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti …pe…**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13076]="*seyyathāpi gihinī kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[13077]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13078]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā sabbanīlakāni cīvarāni dhāretabbāni …pe…**“A nun should not wear entirely blue robes, entirely yellow robes, entirely red robes, entirely magenta robes, entirely black robes, entirely orange robes, entirely beige robes, robes with borders made from a single piece of cloth, robes with long borders, robes with floral borders, robes with borders decorated with fruit designs, close-fitting jackets,*";
P_HTM[13079]="*na tirīṭakaṃ dhāretabbaṃ.**or lodh tree robes.*";
P_HTM[13080]="*Yā dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[13081]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā bhikkhunī kālaṃ karontī evamāha—**On one occasion a nun who was dying said,*";
P_HTM[13082]="*“mamaccayena mayhaṃ parikkhāro saṅghassa hotū”ti.**“When I’m dead, give my requisites to the Sangha.”*";
P_HTM[13083]="*Tattha bhikkhū ca bhikkhuniyo ca vivadanti—**The monks and the nuns argued with one another, saying*";
P_HTM[13084]="*“amhākaṃ hoti, amhākaṃ hotī”ti.**it belonged to their Sangha.*";
P_HTM[13085]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13086]="*“Bhikkhunī ce, bhikkhave, kālaṃ karontī evaṃ vadeyya—**“If a dying nun,*";
P_HTM[13087]="*‘mamaccayena mayhaṃ parikkhāro saṅghassa hotū’ti, anissaro tattha bhikkhusaṅgho, bhikkhunisaṅghassevetaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[13088]="*Sikkhamānā ce, bhikkhave …pe…**a dying trainee nun,*";
P_HTM[13089]="*sāmaṇerī ce, bhikkhave, kālaṃ karontī evaṃ vadeyya—**or a dying novice nun says,*";
P_HTM[13090]="*‘mamaccayena mayhaṃ parikkhāro saṅghassa hotū’ti, anissaro tattha bhikkhusaṅgho, bhikkhunisaṅghassevetaṃ.**‘When I’m dead, give my requisites to the Sangha,’ then they are for the Sangha of nuns, not for the Sangha of monks.*";
P_HTM[13091]="*Bhikkhu ce, bhikkhave, kālaṃ karonto evaṃ vadeyya—**But if a dying monk,*";
P_HTM[13092]="*‘mamaccayena mayhaṃ parikkhāro saṅghassa hotū’ti, anissaro tattha bhikkhunisaṅgho, bhikkhusaṅghassevetaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[13093]="*Sāmaṇero ce, bhikkhave …pe…**a dying novice monk,*";
P_HTM[13094]="*upāsako ce, bhikkhave …pe…**a dying male lay follower,*";
P_HTM[13095]="*upāsikā ce, bhikkhave …pe…**a dying female lay follower,*";
P_HTM[13096]="*añño ce, bhikkhave, koci kālaṃ karonto evaṃ vadeyya—**or anyone else who is dying says,*";
P_HTM[13097]="*‘mamaccayena mayhaṃ parikkhāro saṅghassa hotū’ti, anissaro tattha bhikkhunisaṅgho, bhikkhusaṅghassevetan”ti.**‘When I’m dead, give my requisites to the Sangha,’ then they are for the Sangha of monks, not for the Sangha of nuns.”*";
P_HTM[13098]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā itthī purāṇamallī bhikkhunīsu pabbajitā hoti.**At one time a woman who had been a wrestler went forth as a nun.*";
P_HTM[13099]="*Sā rathikāya dubbalakaṃ bhikkhuṃ passitvā aṃsakūṭena pahāraṃ datvā pātesi.**Seeing a weak monk on a street, she struck him with her shoulder. He fell over.*";
P_HTM[13100]="*Bhikkhū ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[13101]="*“kathañhi nāma, bhikkhunī, bhikkhussa pahāraṃ dassatī”ti.**“How can a nun hit a monk?”*";
P_HTM[13102]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13103]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā bhikkhussa pahāro dātabbo.**“A nun should not hit a monk.*";
P_HTM[13104]="*Yā dadeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13105]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā bhikkhuṃ passitvā dūratova okkamitvā maggaṃ dātun”ti.**When a nun sees a monk coming, she should make way for him by stepping off the path.”*";
P_HTM[13106]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā itthī pavutthapatikā jārena gabbhinī hoti.**At one time a certain woman became pregnant by a lover while her husband was away.*";
P_HTM[13107]="*Sā gabbhaṃ pātetvā kulūpikaṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca—**After having an abortion, she said to the nun who was associating with her family,*";
P_HTM[13108]="*“handayye, imaṃ gabbhaṃ pattena nīharā”ti.**“Venerable, please take this fetus away in your almsbowl.”*";
P_HTM[13109]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī taṃ gabbhaṃ patte pakkhipitvā saṅghāṭiyā paṭicchādetvā agamāsi.**The nun did as asked, hid her bowl under her upper robe, and left.*";
P_HTM[13110]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarena piṇḍacārikena bhikkhunā samādānaṃ kataṃ hoti—**At that time a certain alms-collecting monk had resolved*";
P_HTM[13111]="*“yāhaṃ paṭhamaṃ bhikkhaṃ labhissāmi, na taṃ adatvā bhikkhussa vā bhikkhuniyā vā paribhuñjissāmī”ti.**not to eat without giving the first almsfood he got to another monk or nun.*";
P_HTM[13112]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu taṃ bhikkhuniṃ passitvā etadavoca—**He saw that nun and said,*";
P_HTM[13113]="*“handa, bhagini, bhikkhaṃ paṭiggaṇhā”ti.**“Sister, please accept some almsfood.”*";
P_HTM[13114]="*“Alaṃ, ayyā”ti.**“There is no need, Venerable.”*";
P_HTM[13115]="*Dutiyampi kho …pe…**He repeated his request a second*";
P_HTM[13116]="*tatiyampi kho so bhikkhu taṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca—**and a third time,*";
P_HTM[13117]="*“handa, bhagini, bhikkhaṃ paṭiggaṇhā”ti.**“Sister, please accept some almsfood”,*";
P_HTM[13118]="*“Alaṃ, ayyā”ti.**but received the same reply.*";
P_HTM[13119]="*“Mayā kho, bhagini, samādānaṃ kataṃ—**He then told her about*";
P_HTM[13120]="*‘yāhaṃ paṭhamaṃ bhikkhaṃ labhissāmi, na taṃ adatvā bhikkhussa vā bhikkhuniyā vā paribhuñjissāmī’ti.**his resolution*";
P_HTM[13121]="*Handa, bhagini, bhikkhaṃ paṭiggaṇhā”ti.**and again requested her to accept some almsfood.*";
P_HTM[13122]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī tena bhikkhunā nippīḷiyamānā nīharitvā pattaṃ dassesi—**Being pressured by that monk, the nun brought out her bowl and showed it to him, saying,*";
P_HTM[13123]="*“passa, ayya, patte gabbhaṃ;**“See, there is a fetus in my bowl.*";
P_HTM[13124]="*mā ca kassaci ārocesī”ti.**Please don’t tell anyone.”*";
P_HTM[13125]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**But he complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[13126]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhunī pattena gabbhaṃ nīharissatī”ti.**“How can a nun take a fetus away in her bowl?”*";
P_HTM[13127]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**And he told the monks.*";
P_HTM[13128]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[13129]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhunī pattena gabbhaṃ nīharissatī”ti.**“How can a nun take a fetus away in her bowl?”*";
P_HTM[13130]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13131]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā pattena gabbho nīharitabbo.**“A nun should not take a fetus away in her bowl.*";
P_HTM[13132]="*Yā nīhareyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13133]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā bhikkhuṃ passitvā nīharitvā pattaṃ dassetun”ti.**When a nun sees a monk, she should bring out her almsbowl and show it to him.”*";
P_HTM[13134]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhuṃ passitvā parivattetvā pattamūlaṃ dassenti.**Soon afterwards, when they saw a monk, the nuns from the group of six turned their bowls upside down and showed him the bottom.*";
P_HTM[13135]="*Bhikkhū ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13136]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhuṃ passitvā parivattetvā pattamūlaṃ dassessantī”ti.**“How can the nuns from the group of six do this?”*";
P_HTM[13137]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13138]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā bhikkhuṃ passitvā parivattetvā pattamūlaṃ dassetabbaṃ.**“When she sees a monk, a nun should not turn her almsbowl upside down and show him the bottom.*";
P_HTM[13139]="*Yā dasseyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13140]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā bhikkhuṃ passitvā ukkujjitvā pattaṃ dassetuṃ.**When a nun sees a monk, she should turn her bowl upright and then show it to him.*";
P_HTM[13141]="*Yañca patte āmisaṃ hoti, tena ca bhikkhu nimantetabbo”ti.**And she should offer whatever food is in her bowl to that monk.”*";
P_HTM[13142]="*Tena kho pana samayena sāvatthiyaṃ rathikāya purisabyañjanaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ hoti.**On one occasion a penis had been thrown out on a street in Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[13143]="*Taṃ bhikkhuniyo sakkaccaṃ upanijjhāyiṃsu.**The nuns stared at it.*";
P_HTM[13144]="*Manussā ukkuṭṭhiṃ akaṃsu.**People jeered at them*";
P_HTM[13145]="*Tā bhikkhuniyo maṅkū ahesuṃ.**and the nuns felt humiliated.*";
P_HTM[13146]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo upassayaṃ gantvā bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**When they had returned to the nuns’ dwelling place, they told the nuns what had happened.*";
P_HTM[13147]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13148]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo purisabyañjanaṃ upanijjhāyissantī”ti.**“How can the nuns stare at a penis?”*";
P_HTM[13149]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the monks,*";
P_HTM[13150]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**who in turn told the Buddha. He said,*";
P_HTM[13151]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā purisabyañjanaṃ upanijjhāyitabbaṃ.**“A nun should not stare at a penis.*";
P_HTM[13152]="*Yā upanijjhāyeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[13153]="*Tena kho pana samayena manussā bhikkhūnaṃ āmisaṃ denti.**On one occasion people gave requisites to the monks*";
P_HTM[13154]="*Bhikkhū bhikkhunīnaṃ denti.**and the monks gave them to the nuns.*";
P_HTM[13155]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13156]="*“kathañhi nāma bhadantā attano paribhogatthāya dinnaṃ aññesaṃ dassanti.**“How can the venerables give away to others what has been given to them for their own use?*";
P_HTM[13157]="*Mayampi na jānāma dānaṃ dātun”ti.**Do we not know how to give?”*";
P_HTM[13158]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13159]="*“Na, bhikkhave, attano paribhogatthāya dinnaṃ aññesaṃ dātabbaṃ.**“Monks, you should not give away to others what has been given to you for your own use.*";
P_HTM[13160]="*Yo dadeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[13161]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhūnaṃ āmisaṃ ussannaṃ hoti.**On one occasion the monks had an abundance of requisites.*";
P_HTM[13162]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13163]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, saṅghassa dātun”ti.**“I allow you to give to a sangha.”*";
P_HTM[13164]="*Bāḷhataraṃ ussannaṃ hoti.**The abundance became even greater.*";
P_HTM[13165]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13166]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, puggalikampi dātun”ti.**“I allow individuals to give away what belongs to them.”*";
P_HTM[13167]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhūnaṃ sannidhikataṃ āmisaṃ ussannaṃ hoti.**On one occasion the monks had an abundance of requisites stored up.*";
P_HTM[13168]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13169]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ sannidhiṃ bhikkhunīhi paṭiggāhāpetvā paribhuñjitun”ti.**“I allow what is stored by the monks to be received by the nuns and then used by them.”*";
P_HTM[13170]="*Tena kho pana samayena manussā bhikkhunīnaṃ āmisaṃ denti.**On one occasion people gave requisites to the nuns*";
P_HTM[13171]="*Bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ denti.**and the nuns gave them to the monks.*";
P_HTM[13172]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13173]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo attano paribhogatthāya dinnaṃ aññesaṃ dassanti.**“How can the nuns give away to others what has been given to them for their own use?*";
P_HTM[13174]="*Mayampi na jānāma dānaṃ dātun”ti.**Do we not know how to give?”*";
P_HTM[13175]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13176]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā attano paribhogatthāya dinnaṃ aññesaṃ dātabbaṃ.**“A nun should not give away to others what has been given to her for her own use.*";
P_HTM[13177]="*Yā dadeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If she does, scommits an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[13178]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhunīnaṃ āmisaṃ ussannaṃ hoti.**On one occasion the nuns had an abundance of requisites.*";
P_HTM[13179]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13180]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, saṅghassa dātun”ti.**“I allow a nun to give to the Sangha.”*";
P_HTM[13181]="*Bāḷhataraṃ ussannaṃ hoti.**The abundance became even greater.*";
P_HTM[13182]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13183]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, puggalikampi dātun”ti.**“I allow individuals to give away what belongs to them.”*";
P_HTM[13184]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhunīnaṃ sannidhikataṃ āmisaṃ ussannaṃ hoti.**On one occasion the nuns had an abundance of requisites stored up.*";
P_HTM[13185]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13186]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhunīnaṃ sannidhiṃ bhikkhūhi paṭiggāhāpetvā paribhuñjitun”ti.**“I allow what is stored by the nuns to be received by the monks and then used by them.”*";
P_HTM[13187]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhūnaṃ senāsanaṃ ussannaṃ hoti, bhikkhunīnaṃ na hoti.**On one occasion the monks had an abundance of dwellings, but the nuns were lacking.*";
P_HTM[13188]="*Bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ santike dūtaṃ pāhesuṃ—**The nuns sent a message to the monks, saying,*";
P_HTM[13189]="*“sādhu, bhante, ayyā amhākaṃ senāsanaṃ dentu tāvakālikan”ti.**“It would be good, Venerables, if you would lend us some dwellings.”*";
P_HTM[13190]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13191]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhunīnaṃ senāsanaṃ dātuṃ tāvakālikan”ti.**“I allow you to lend dwellings to the nuns.”*";
P_HTM[13192]="*Tena kho pana samayena utuniyo bhikkhuniyo onaddhamañcaṃ onaddhapīṭhaṃ abhinisīdantipi abhinipajjantipi.**Menstruating nuns sat down and lay down on upholstered beds and benches.*";
P_HTM[13193]="*Senāsanaṃ lohitena makkhiyyati.**The furniture was stained with blood.*";
P_HTM[13194]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13195]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā onaddhamañcaṃ onaddhapīṭhaṃ abhinisīditabbaṃ abhinipajjitabbaṃ.**“A nun should not sit down or lay down on upholstered beds or benches.*";
P_HTM[13196]="*Yā abhinisīdeyya vā abhinipajjeyya vā āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13197]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, āvasathacīvaran”ti.**I allow a monastery robe.”*";
P_HTM[13198]="*Āvasathacīvaraṃ lohitena makkhiyyati.**The monastery robe became stained with blood.*";
P_HTM[13199]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13200]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, āṇicoḷakan”ti.**“I allow a menstruation pad .”*";
P_HTM[13201]="*Coḷakaṃ nipatati.**The pad fell off.*";
P_HTM[13202]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13203]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, suttakena bandhitvā ūruyā bandhitun”ti.**“I allow the nuns to attach a string and then bind it to the thigh.”*";
P_HTM[13204]="*Suttaṃ chijjati.**The string snapped.*";
P_HTM[13205]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13206]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, saṃvelliyaṃ, kaṭisuttakan”ti.**“I allow a loin cloth and a girdle.”*";
P_HTM[13207]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo sabbakālaṃ kaṭisuttakaṃ dhārenti.**Soon afterwards the nuns from the group of six wore girdles all the time.*";
P_HTM[13208]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13209]="*“seyyathāpi gihinī kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[13210]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13211]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā sabbakālaṃ kaṭisuttakaṃ dhāretabbaṃ.**“A nun should not wear a girdle all the time.*";
P_HTM[13212]="*Yā dhāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13213]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, utuniyā kaṭisuttakan”ti.**I allow a nun to wear a girdle while she is menstruating.”*";
P_HTM[13214]="*Dutiyabhāṇavāro niṭṭhito.**The second section for recitation is finished.*";
P_HTM[13215]="*Tena kho pana samayena upasampannāyo dissanti—**At that time the full ordination had been given to*";
P_HTM[13216]="*animittāpi, nimittamattāpi, alohitāpi, dhuvalohitāpi, dhuvacoḷāpi, paggharantīpi, sikharaṇīpi, itthipaṇḍakāpi, vepurisikāpi, sambhinnāpi, ubhatobyañjanāpi.**women who lacked genitals, who had incomplete genitals, who did not menstruate, who menstruated continuously, who always wore menstruation pads, who were incontinent, who had genital prolapse, who lacked sexual organs, who were manlike, who had fistula, who were hermaphrodites.*";
P_HTM[13217]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13218]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, upasampādentiyā catuvīsati antarāyike dhamme pucchituṃ.**“The nun who is giving the full ordination should ask about the twenty-four impediments.*";
P_HTM[13219]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, pucchitabbā—**And it should be done like this:*";
P_HTM[13220]="*‘nasi animittā, nasi nimittamattā, nasi alohitā, nasi dhuvalohitā, nasi dhuvacoḷā, nasi paggharantī, nasi sikharaṇī, nasi itthipaṇḍakā, nasi vepurisikā, nasi sambhinnā, nasi ubhatobyañjanā?**ʻDo you lack genitals? Are your genitals incomplete? Are you without menstruation? Do you menstruate continuously? Do you always wear a menstruation pad? Are you incontinent? Do you have genital prolapse? Do you lack sexual organs? Are you manlike? Do you have fistula? Are you a hermaphrodite?*";
P_HTM[13221]="*Santi te evarūpā ābādhā—**Do you have any of these diseases:*";
P_HTM[13222]="*kuṭṭhaṃ, gaṇḍo, kilāso, soso, apamāro?**leprosy, abscesses, mild leprosy, tuberculosis, or epilepsy?*";
P_HTM[13223]="*Manussāsi, itthīsi, bhujissāsi, aṇaṇāsi, nasi rājabhaṭī?**Are you human? Are you a woman? Are you free from slavery? Are you free from debt? Are you employed by the King?*";
P_HTM[13224]="*Anuññātāsi mātāpitūhi, sāmikena?**Do you have permission from your parents and husband?*";
P_HTM[13225]="*Paripuṇṇavīsativassāsi, paripuṇṇaṃ te pattacīvaraṃ, kiṃnāmāsi, kānāmā te pavattinī’”ti?**Are you twenty years old? Do you have a full set of bowl and robes? What is your name? What is the name of your mentor?’”*";
P_HTM[13226]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū bhikkhunīnaṃ antarāyike dhamme pucchanti.**Soon afterwards the monks asked the nuns about the impediments.*";
P_HTM[13227]="*Upasampadāpekkhāyo vitthāyanti, maṅkū honti, na sakkonti vissajjetuṃ.**Those seeking the full ordination were embarrassed, humiliated, and unable to respond.*";
P_HTM[13228]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13229]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ekatoupasampannāya bhikkhunisaṅghe visuddhāya bhikkhusaṅghe upasampādetun”ti.**“Only when a woman who is free from impediments has been fully ordained on one side in the Sangha of nuns, should you give her the full ordination in the Sangha of monks.”*";
P_HTM[13230]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo ananusiṭṭhā upasampadāpekkhāyo antarāyike dhamme pucchanti.**The nuns asked those seeking the full ordination about the impediments without first instructing them.*";
P_HTM[13231]="*Upasampadāpekkhāyo vitthāyanti, maṅkū honti, na sakkonti vissajjetuṃ.**They were embarrassed, humiliated, and unable to respond.*";
P_HTM[13232]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13233]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, paṭhamaṃ anusāsitvā pacchā antarāyike dhamme pucchitun”ti.**“The nuns should instruct first and then ask about the impediments.”*";
P_HTM[13234]="*Tattheva saṅghamajjhe anusāsanti.**They instructed them right there in the midst of the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[13235]="*Upasampadāpekkhāyo tatheva vitthāyanti, maṅkū honti, na sakkonti vissajjetuṃ.**Once again those seeking the full ordination were embarrassed, humiliated, and unable to respond.*";
P_HTM[13236]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13237]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ekamantaṃ anusāsitvā saṅghamajjhe antarāyike dhamme pucchituṃ.**“The nuns should instruct them at a distance and then ask about the impediments in the midst of the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[13238]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, anusāsitabbā.**And it should be done like this.*";
P_HTM[13239]="*Paṭhamaṃ upajjhaṃ gāhāpetabbā.**First the candidate should be told to choose a preceptor.*";
P_HTM[13240]="*Upajjhaṃ gāhāpetvā pattacīvaraṃ ācikkhitabbaṃ—**Her bowl and robes should then be pointed out to her:*";
P_HTM[13241]="*‘ayaṃ te patto, ayaṃ saṅghāṭi, ayaṃ uttarāsaṅgo, ayaṃ antaravāsako, idaṃ saṅkaccikaṃ, ayaṃ udakasāṭikā;**ʻThis is your bowl, this your outer robe, this your upper robe, this your sarong, this is your chest wrap, and this is your bathing robe.*";
P_HTM[13242]="*gaccha amumhi okāse tiṭṭhāhī’”ti.**Now please go and stand over there.’”*";
P_HTM[13243]="*Bālā abyattā anusāsanti.**They were instructed by nuns who were ignorant and incompetent.*";
P_HTM[13244]="*Duranusiṭṭhā upasampadāpekkhāyo vitthāyanti, maṅkū honti, na sakkonti vissajjetuṃ.**And because they were badly instructed, they were once again embarrassed, humiliated, and unable to respond.*";
P_HTM[13245]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13246]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bālāya abyattāya anusāsitabbā.**“A nun who is ignorant and incompetent should not instruct.*";
P_HTM[13247]="*Yā anusāseyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13248]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya anusāsitun”ti.**A nun who is competent and capable should instruct.”*";
P_HTM[13249]="*Asammatā anusāsanti.**They instructed without having been appointed.*";
P_HTM[13250]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13251]="*“Na, bhikkhave, asammatāya anusāsitabbā.**“A nun should not instruct if she hasn’t been appointed to do so.*";
P_HTM[13252]="*Yā anusāseyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13253]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, sammatāya anusāsituṃ.**I allow a nun to instruct if she’s been appointed to do so.*";
P_HTM[13254]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sammannitabbā—**And it should be done like this:*";
P_HTM[13255]="*attanā vā attānaṃ sammannitabbaṃ, parāya vā parā sammannitabbā.**either one should be appointed through oneself or one should be appointed through another.*";
P_HTM[13256]="*Kathañca attanāva attānaṃ sammannitabbaṃ?**And how is one appointed through oneself?*";
P_HTM[13257]="*Byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable nun should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[13258]="*‘suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13259]="*Itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya upasampadāpekkhā.**So-and-so is seeking the full ordination with Venerable so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13260]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, ahaṃ itthannāmā itthannāmaṃ anusāseyyan’ti.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, I will instruct so-and-so.’*";
P_HTM[13261]="*Evaṃ attanāva attānaṃ sammannitabbaṃ.**In this way one is appointed through oneself.*";
P_HTM[13262]="*Kathañca parāya parā sammannitabbā?**And how is one appointed through another?*";
P_HTM[13263]="*Byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable nun should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[13264]="*‘suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13265]="*Itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya upasampadāpekkhā.**So-and-so is seeking the full ordination with Venerable so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13266]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, itthannāmā itthannāmaṃ anusāseyyā’ti.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, so-and-so will instruct so-and-so.’*";
P_HTM[13267]="*Evaṃ parāya parā sammannitabbā.**In this way one is appointed through another.*";
P_HTM[13268]="*Tāya sammatāya bhikkhuniyā upasampadāpekkhaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyā—**The appointed nun should go to the one seeking the full ordination and say this:*";
P_HTM[13269]="*‘suṇasi itthannāme.**ʻListen, so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13270]="*Ayaṃ te saccakālo, bhūtakālo.**Now is the time for you to tell the truth.*";
P_HTM[13271]="*Yaṃ jātaṃ taṃ saṅghamajjhe pucchante santaṃ atthīti vattabbaṃ, asantaṃ natthīti vattabbaṃ.**When asked in the midst of the Sangha about various matters, you should say, “Yes,” if it’s true and, “No,” if it’s not.*";
P_HTM[13272]="*Mā kho vitthāyi, mā kho maṅku ahosi.**Don’t be embarrassed or humiliated.*";
P_HTM[13273]="*Evaṃ taṃ pucchissanti—**This is what they will ask you:*";
P_HTM[13274]="*nasi animittā, nasi nimittamattā, nasi alohitā, nasi dhuvalohitā, nasi dhuvacoḷā, nasi paggharantī, nasi sikharaṇī, nasi itthipaṇḍakā, nasi vepurisikā, nasi sambhinnā, nasi ubhatobyañjanā?**“Do you lack genitals? Are your genitals incomplete? Are you without menstruation? Do you menstruate continuously? Do you always wear a menstruation pad? Are you incontinent? Do you have genital prolapse? Do you lack sexual organs? Are you manlike? Do you have fistula? Are you a hermaphrodite?*";
P_HTM[13275]="*Santi te evarūpā ābādhā—**Do you have any of these diseases:*";
P_HTM[13276]="*kuṭṭhaṃ, gaṇḍo, kilāso, soso, apamāro?**leprosy, abscesses, mild leprosy, tuberculosis, or epilepsy?*";
P_HTM[13277]="*Manussāsi, itthīsi, bhujissāsi, aṇaṇāsi, nasi rājabhaṭī?**Are you human? Are you a woman? Are you free from slavery? Are you free from debt? Are you employed by the King?*";
P_HTM[13278]="*Anuññātāsi mātāpitūhi, sāmikena?**Do you have permission from your parents and husband?*";
P_HTM[13279]="*Paripuṇṇavīsativassāsi, paripuṇṇaṃ te pattacīvaraṃ, kiṃnāmāsi, kānāmā te pavattinī’ti?**Are you twenty years old? Do you have a full set of bowl and robes? What is your name? What is the name of your mentor?”’”*";
P_HTM[13280]="*Ekato āgacchanti.**They then returned to the Sangha together. The Buddha said,*";
P_HTM[13281]="*Na ekato āgantabbaṃ.**“They should not return together.*";
P_HTM[13282]="*Anusāsikāya paṭhamataraṃ āgantvā saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**The instructor should return first and inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[13283]="*‘suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13284]="*Itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya upasampadāpekkhā.**So-and-so is seeking the full ordination with Venerable so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13285]="*Anusiṭṭhā sā mayā.**She’s been instructed by me.*";
P_HTM[13286]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, itthannāmā āgaccheyyā’ti.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, so-and-so should come.’*";
P_HTM[13287]="*‘Āgacchāhī’ti vattabbā.**And she should be told to come.*";
P_HTM[13288]="*Ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ kārāpetvā bhikkhunīnaṃ pāde vandāpetvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīdāpetvā añjaliṃ paggaṇhāpetvā upasampadaṃ yācāpetabbā—**She should then put her upper robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the nuns, squat on her heels, and raise her joined palms. She should then ask for the full ordination:*";
P_HTM[13289]="*‘saṅghaṃ, ayye, upasampadaṃ yācāmi.**‘Venerables, I ask the Sangha for the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13290]="*Ullumpatu maṃ, ayye, saṅgho anukampaṃ upādāya.**Please lift me up out of compassion.’*";
P_HTM[13291]="*Dutiyampi, ayye, saṅghaṃ upasampadaṃ yācāmi.**For the second time, Venerables, I ask the Sangha for the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13292]="*Ullumpatu maṃ, ayye, saṅgho anukampaṃ upādāya.**Please lift me up out of compassion.’*";
P_HTM[13293]="*Tatiyampi, ayye, saṅghaṃ upasampadaṃ yācāmi.**For the third time, Venerables, I ask the Sangha for the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13294]="*Ullumpatu maṃ, ayye, saṅgho anukampaṃ upādāyā’ti.**Please lift me up out of compassion.’*";
P_HTM[13295]="*Byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable nun should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[13296]="*‘Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13297]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya upasampadāpekkhā.**So-and-so is seeking the full ordination with Venerable so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13298]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, ahaṃ itthannāmaṃ antarāyike dhamme puccheyyanti.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, I will ask so-and-so about the impediments.*";
P_HTM[13299]="*Suṇasi itthannāme.**Listen, so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13300]="*Ayaṃ te saccakālo, bhūtakālo.**Now is the time for you to tell the truth.*";
P_HTM[13301]="*Yaṃ jātaṃ taṃ pucchāmi santaṃ atthīti vattabbaṃ, asantaṃ natthīti vattabbaṃ.**I will ask you about various matters. If something is true, you should say, “Yes,” and if it’s not, you should say, “No.”*";
P_HTM[13302]="*Nasi animittā …pe…**So: Do you lack genitals? Are your genitals incomplete? Are you without menstruation? Do you menstruate continuously? Do you always wear a menstruation pad? Are you incontinent? Do you have genital prolapse? Do you lack sexual organs? Are you manlike? Do you have fistula? Are you a hermaphrodite? Do you have any of these diseases: leprosy, abscesses, mild leprosy, tuberculosis, or epilepsy? Are you human? Are you a woman? Are you free from slavery? Are you free from debt? Are you employed by the King? Do you have permission from your parents and husband? Are you twenty years old? Do you have a full set of bowl and robes?*";
P_HTM[13303]="*kiṃnāmāsi, kānāmā te pavattinī’ti.**What is your name? What is the name of your mentor?’*";
P_HTM[13304]="*Byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable nun should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[13305]="*‘Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13306]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya upasampadāpekkhā.**So-and-so is seeking the full ordination with Venerable so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13307]="*Parisuddhā antarāyikehi dhammehi, paripuṇṇassā pattacīvaraṃ.**She is free from obstructions and her bowl and robes are complete.*";
P_HTM[13308]="*Itthannāmā saṅghaṃ upasampadaṃ yācati itthannāmāya ayyāya pavattiniyā.**So-and-so is asking the Sangha for the full ordination with so-and-so as her mentor.*";
P_HTM[13309]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmaṃ upasampādeyya itthannāmāya ayyāya pavattiniyā.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should give the full ordination to so-and-so with so-and-so as her mentor.*";
P_HTM[13310]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[13311]="*Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13312]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya upasampadāpekkhā.**So-and-so is seeking the full ordination with Venerable so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13313]="*Parisuddhā antarāyikehi dhammehi, paripuṇṇassā pattacīvaraṃ.**She is free from obstructions and her bowl and robes are complete.*";
P_HTM[13314]="*Itthannāmā saṅghaṃ upasampadaṃ yācati itthannāmāya ayyāya pavattiniyā.**So-and-so is asking the Sangha for the full ordination with so-and-so as her mentor.*";
P_HTM[13315]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ upasampādeti itthannāmāya ayyāya pavattiniyā.**The Sangha gives the full ordination to so-and-so with so-and-so as her mentor.*";
P_HTM[13316]="*Yassā ayyāya khamati itthannāmāya upasampadā itthannāmāya ayyāya pavattiniyā, sā tuṇhassa;**Any nun who approves of giving the full ordination to so-and-so with so-and-so as her mentor should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[13317]="*yassā nakkhamati, sā bhāseyya.**Any nun who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[13318]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter. Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen. So-and-so is seeking the full ordination with Venerable so-and-so. She is free from obstructions and her bowl and robes are complete. So-and-so is asking the Sangha for the full ordination with so-and-so as her preceptor. The Sangha gives the full ordination to so-and-so with so-and-so as her preceptor. Any nun who approves of giving the full ordination to so-and-so with so-and-so as her preceptor should remain silent. Any nun who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[13319]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—**For the third time I speak on this matter.*";
P_HTM[13320]="*suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13321]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya upasampadāpekkhā.**So-and-so is seeking the full ordination with Venerable so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13322]="*Parisuddhā antarāyikehi dhammehi, paripuṇṇassā pattacīvaraṃ.**She is free from obstructions and her bowl and robes are complete.*";
P_HTM[13323]="*Itthannāmā saṅghaṃ upasampadaṃ yācati itthannāmāya ayyāya pavattiniyā.**So-and-so is asking the Sangha for the full ordination with so-and-so as her mentor.*";
P_HTM[13324]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ upasampādeti itthannāmāya ayyāya pavattiniyā.**The Sangha gives the full ordination to so-and-so with so-and-so as her mentor.*";
P_HTM[13325]="*Yassā ayyāya khamati itthannāmāya upasampadā itthannāmāya ayyāya pavattiniyā, sā tuṇhassa;**Any nun who approves of giving the full ordination to so-and-so with so-and-so as her mentor should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[13326]="*yassā nakkhamati, sā bhāseyya.**Any nun who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[13327]="*Upasampannā saṅghena itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya pavattiniyā.**The Sangha has given the full ordination to so-and-so with so-and-so as her mentor.*";
P_HTM[13328]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[13329]="*Tāvadeva taṃ ādāya bhikkhusaṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ kārāpetvā bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vandāpetvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīdāpetvā añjaliṃ paggaṇhāpetvā upasampadaṃ yācāpetabbā—**“Straightaway she should be taken to the Sangha of monks. She should put her upper robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the monks, squat on her heels, and raise her joined palms. She should then ask for ordination:*";
P_HTM[13330]="*‘ahaṃ, ayyā, itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya upasampadāpekkhā.**‘Venerables, I’m seeking the full ordination with Venerable so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13331]="*Ekatoupasampannā bhikkhunisaṅghe, visuddhā;**I’m free from impediments and have been fully ordained on one side in the Sangha of nuns.*";
P_HTM[13332]="*saṅghaṃ, ayyā, upasampadaṃ yācāmi.**I ask the Sangha for the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13333]="*Ullumpatu maṃ, ayyā, saṅgho anukampaṃ upādāya.**Please lift me up out of compassion.’*";
P_HTM[13334]="*Ahaṃ, ayyā, itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya upasampadāpekkhā.**Venerables, I’m seeking the full ordination with Venerable so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13335]="*Ekatoupasampannā bhikkhunisaṅghe, visuddhā.**I’m free from impediments and have been fully ordained on one side in the Sangha of nuns.*";
P_HTM[13336]="*Dutiyampi, ayyā, saṅghaṃ upasampadaṃ yācāmi.**For the second time I ask the Sangha for the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13337]="*Ullumpatu maṃ, ayyā, saṅgho anukampaṃ upādāya.**Please lift me up out of compassion.’*";
P_HTM[13338]="*Ahaṃ, ayyā, itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya upasampadāpekkhā.**Venerables, I’m seeking the full ordination with Venerable so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13339]="*Ekatoupasampannā bhikkhunisaṅghe, visuddhā.**I’m free from impediments and have been fully ordained on one side in the Sangha of nuns.*";
P_HTM[13340]="*Tatiyampi, ayyā, saṅghaṃ upasampadaṃ yācāmi.**For the third time I ask the Sangha for the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13341]="*Ullumpatu maṃ, ayyā, saṅgho anukampaṃ upādāyā’ti.**Please lift me up out of compassion.’*";
P_HTM[13342]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[13343]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13344]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā itthannāmāya upasampadāpekkhā.**So-and-so is seeking the full ordination with Venerable so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13345]="*Ekatoupasampannā bhikkhunisaṅghe, visuddhā.**She is free from impediments and has been fully ordained on one side in the Sangha of nuns.*";
P_HTM[13346]="*Itthannāmā saṅghaṃ upasampadaṃ yācati itthannāmāya pavattiniyā.**She is asking the Sangha for the full ordination with so-and-so as her mentor.*";
P_HTM[13347]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmaṃ upasampādeyya, itthannāmāya pavattiniyā.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should give her the full ordination with so-and-so as her mentor.*";
P_HTM[13348]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[13349]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13350]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā itthannāmāya upasampadāpekkhā.**So-and-so is seeking the full ordination with Venerable so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13351]="*Ekatoupasampannā bhikkhunisaṅghe, visuddhā.**She is free from impediments and has been fully ordained on one side in the Sangha of nuns.*";
P_HTM[13352]="*Itthannāmā saṅghaṃ upasampadaṃ yācati itthannāmāya pavattiniyā.**So-and-so is asking the Sangha for the full ordination with so-and-so as her mentor.*";
P_HTM[13353]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ upasampādeti itthannāmāya pavattiniyā.**The Sangha gives her the full ordination with so-and-so as her mentor.*";
P_HTM[13354]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmāya upasampadā itthannāmāya pavattiniyā, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of giving so-and-so the full ordination with so-and-so as her mentor should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[13355]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[13356]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter. Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen. So-and-so is seeking the full ordination with Venerable so-and-so. She is free from impediments and has been fully ordained on one side in the Sangha of nuns. So-and-so is asking the Sangha for the full ordination with so-and-so as her preceptor. The Sangha gives her the full ordination with so-and-so as her preceptor. Any monk who approves of giving so-and-so the full ordination with so-and-so as her preceptor should remain silent. Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[13357]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—**For the third time I speak on this matter.*";
P_HTM[13358]="*suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13359]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā itthannāmāya upasampadāpekkhā.**So-and-so is seeking the full ordination with Venerable so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13360]="*Ekatoupasampannā bhikkhunisaṅghe, visuddhā.**She is free from impediments and has been fully ordained on one side in the Sangha of nuns.*";
P_HTM[13361]="*Itthannāmā saṅghaṃ upasampadaṃ yācati itthannāmāya pavattiniyā.**So-and-so is asking the Sangha for the full ordination with so-and-so as her mentor.*";
P_HTM[13362]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ upasampādeti itthannāmāya pavattiniyā.**The Sangha gives her the full ordination with so-and-so as her mentor.*";
P_HTM[13363]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmāya upasampadā itthannāmāya pavattiniyā, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of giving so-and-so the full ordination with so-and-so as her mentor should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[13364]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[13365]="*Upasampannā saṅghena itthannāmā itthannāmāya pavattiniyā.**The Sangha has given so-and-so the full ordination with so-and-so as her mentor.*";
P_HTM[13366]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[13367]="*Tāvadeva chāyā metabbā, utuppamāṇaṃ ācikkhitabbaṃ, divasabhāgo ācikkhitabbo, saṅgīti ācikkhitabbā, bhikkhuniyo vattabbā—**Straightaway the time should be noted and the date should be pointed out. These should be declared jointly to everyone.*";
P_HTM[13368]="*imissā tayo ca nissaye, aṭṭha ca akaraṇīyāni ācikkheyyāthā”ti.**The nuns should be told to point out the three supports and the eight things not to be done to the newly ordained nun.*";
P_HTM[13369]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo bhattagge āsanaṃ saṅkasāyantiyo kālaṃ vītināmesuṃ.**On one occasion the right time for eating passed while the nuns were trying to find the right seats in the dining hall.*";
P_HTM[13370]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13371]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, aṭṭhannaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ yathāvuḍḍhaṃ, avasesānaṃ yathāgatikan”ti.**“I allow eight nuns to be seated according to seniority, but the rest according to their time of arrival.”*";
P_HTM[13372]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo—**When they knew about*";
P_HTM[13373]="*“bhagavatā anuññātaṃ aṭṭhannaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ yathāvuḍḍhaṃ, avasesānaṃ yathāgatikan”ti—**the Buddha’s allowance,*";
P_HTM[13374]="*sabbattha aṭṭheva bhikkhuniyo yathāvuḍḍhaṃ paṭibāhanti, avasesāyo yathāgatikaṃ.**eight nuns reserved places everywhere according to seniority, the rest getting places according to their time of arrival.*";
P_HTM[13375]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13376]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhattagge aṭṭhannaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ yathāvuḍḍhaṃ, avasesānaṃ yathāgatikaṃ;**“I allow eight nuns to be seated in the dining hall according to seniority and the rest according to their time of arrival,*";
P_HTM[13377]="*aññattha sabbattha yathāvuḍḍhaṃ na paṭibāhitabbaṃ.**but not anywhere else.*";
P_HTM[13378]="*Yā paṭibāheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If a nun makes a reservation anywhere apart from the dining hall, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[13379]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo na pavārenti.**At that time the nuns did not do the invitation procedure.*";
P_HTM[13380]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13381]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā na pavāretabbaṃ.**“A nun should do the invitation procedure.*";
P_HTM[13382]="*Yā na pavāreyya, yathādhammo kāretabbo”ti.**If she doesn’t, she should be dealt with according to the rule.”*";
P_HTM[13383]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo attanā pavāretvā bhikkhusaṅghaṃ na pavārenti.**At that time the nuns did the invitation procedure among themselves, but not with the Sangha of monks.*";
P_HTM[13384]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13385]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā attanā pavāretvā bhikkhusaṅgho na pavāretabbo.**“After doing the invitation procedure among the nuns, a nun should do the invitation procedure with the monks.*";
P_HTM[13386]="*Yā na pavāreyya, yathādhammo kāretabbo”ti.**If she doesn’t, she should be dealt with according to the rule.”*";
P_HTM[13387]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ ekato pavārentiyo kolāhalaṃ akaṃsu.**All the nuns together did the invitation procedure with monks. They made a racket.*";
P_HTM[13388]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13389]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ ekato pavāretabbaṃ.**“The nuns should not do the invitation procedure all together.*";
P_HTM[13390]="*Yā pavāreyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**Any nun who does commits an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[13391]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo purebhattaṃ pavārentiyo kālaṃ vītināmesuṃ.**On one occasion when the nuns did the invitation procedure before the meal, they did not finish until after the time for eating.*";
P_HTM[13392]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13393]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pacchābhattaṃ pavāretun”ti.**“I allow the nuns to do the invitation procedure after the meal.”*";
P_HTM[13394]="*Pacchābhattaṃ pavārentiyo vikāle ahesuṃ.**Doing the invitation procedure after the meal, they did not finish until it was too late to eat.*";
P_HTM[13395]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13396]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ajjatanā bhikkhunisaṅghaṃ pavāretvā aparajju bhikkhusaṅghaṃ pavāretun”ti.**“I allow the nuns to do the invitation procedure among themselves on one day and with the monks on the following day.”*";
P_HTM[13397]="*Tena kho pana samayena sabbo bhikkhunisaṅgho pavārento kolāhalaṃ akāsi.**At that time the whole Sangha of nuns did the invitation procedure. They made a racket.*";
P_HTM[13398]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13399]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ekaṃ bhikkhuniṃ byattaṃ paṭibalaṃ sammannituṃ—**“I allow the nuns to appoint one capable and competent nun*";
P_HTM[13400]="*bhikkhunisaṅghassa atthāya bhikkhusaṅghaṃ pavāretuṃ.**to do the invitation procedure with the Sangha of monks on behalf of the Sangha of nuns.*";
P_HTM[13401]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sammannitabbā.**She should be appointed like this.*";
P_HTM[13402]="*Paṭhamaṃ bhikkhunī yācitabbā, yācitvā byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**First a nun should be asked, and then a competent and capable nun should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[13403]="*‘Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13404]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuniṃ sammanneyya bhikkhunisaṅghassa atthāya bhikkhusaṅghaṃ pavāretuṃ.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should appoint nun so-and-so to do the invitation procedure with the Sangha of monks on behalf of the Sangha of nuns.*";
P_HTM[13405]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[13406]="*Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13407]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuniṃ sammannati bhikkhunisaṅghassa atthāya bhikkhusaṅghaṃ pavāretuṃ.**The Sangha appoints nun so-and-so to do the invitation procedure with the Sangha of monks on behalf of the Sangha of nuns.*";
P_HTM[13408]="*Yassā ayyāya khamati itthannāmāya bhikkhuniyā sammuti bhikkhunisaṅghassa atthāya bhikkhusaṅghaṃ pavāretuṃ, sā tuṇhassa;**Any nun who approves of appointing nun so-and-so to do the invitation procedure with the Sangha of monks on behalf of the Sangha of nuns should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[13409]="*yassā nakkhamati, sā bhāseyya.**Any nun who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[13410]="*Sammatā saṅghena itthannāmā bhikkhunī bhikkhunisaṅghassa atthāya bhikkhusaṅghaṃ pavāretuṃ.**The Sangha has appointed nun so-and-so to do the invitation procedure with the Sangha of monks on behalf of the Sangha of nuns.*";
P_HTM[13411]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[13412]="*Tāya sammatāya bhikkhuniyā bhikkhunisaṅghaṃ ādāya bhikkhusaṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**The appointed nun should take the Sangha of nuns to the Sangha of monks. She should then put her upper robe over one shoulder, squat on her heels, raise her joined palms, and say:*";
P_HTM[13413]="*‘bhikkhunisaṅgho, ayyā, bhikkhusaṅghaṃ pavāreti—**ʻVenerables, the Sangha of nuns invites the Sangha of monks to correct it concerning*";
P_HTM[13414]="*diṭṭhena vā, sutena vā parisaṅkāya vā.**what you have seen, what you have heard, or what you suspect.*";
P_HTM[13415]="*Vadatu, ayyā, bhikkhusaṅgho bhikkhunisaṅghaṃ anukampaṃ upādāya, passanto paṭikarissati.**Please correct the Sangha of nuns, Venerables, out of compassion. If the Sangha of nuns sees a fault, it will make amends.*";
P_HTM[13416]="*Dutiyampi, ayyā …pe…**For the second time the Sangha of nuns invites the Sangha of monks to correct it concerning what you have seen, what you have heard, or what you suspect. Please correct the Sangha of nuns, Venerables, out of compassion. If the Sangha of nuns sees a fault, it will make amends.*";
P_HTM[13417]="*tatiyampi, ayyā, bhikkhunisaṅgho bhikkhusaṅghaṃ pavāreti—**For the third time the Sangha of nuns invites the Sangha of monks to correct it concerning*";
P_HTM[13418]="*diṭṭhena vā, sutena vā, parisaṅkāya vā.**what you have seen, what you have heard, or what you suspect.*";
P_HTM[13419]="*Vadatu, ayyā, bhikkhusaṅgho bhikkhunisaṅghaṃ anukampaṃ upādāya, passanto paṭikarissatī’”ti.**Please correct the Sangha of nuns, Venerables, out of compassion. If the Sangha of nuns sees a fault, it will make amends.’”*";
P_HTM[13420]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ uposathaṃ ṭhapenti, pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapenti, savacanīyaṃ karonti, anuvādaṃ paṭṭhapenti, okāsaṃ kārenti, codenti, sārenti.**At that time the nuns canceled the monks’ observance-day procedure and their invitation procedure; they spoke to them to initiate a legal process against them; they made accusations against them, asked them for permission to accuse them of offenses, accused them of offenses, and reminded them of offenses.*";
P_HTM[13421]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13422]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā bhikkhussa uposatho ṭhapetabbo;**“A nun should not cancel the observance-day procedure of a monk.*";
P_HTM[13423]="*ṭhapitopi aṭṭhapito;**If she does cancel it, it’s not actually canceled,*";
P_HTM[13424]="*ṭhapentiyā āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13425]="*Na pavāraṇā ṭhapetabbā;**A nun should not cancel the invitation procedure of a monk.*";
P_HTM[13426]="*ṭhapitāpi aṭṭhapitā;**If she does cancel it, it’s not actually canceled,*";
P_HTM[13427]="*ṭhapentiyā āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13428]="*Na savacanīyaṃ kātabbaṃ;**A nun should not speak to a monk to initiate a legal process against him.*";
P_HTM[13429]="*katampi akataṃ;**If she does, it’s not actually done,*";
P_HTM[13430]="*karontiyā āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13431]="*Na anuvādo paṭṭhapetabbo;**A nun should not make accusations against a monk.*";
P_HTM[13432]="*paṭṭhapitopi appaṭṭhapito;**If she does, it’s not actually done,*";
P_HTM[13433]="*paṭṭhapentiyā āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13434]="*Na okāso kāretabbo;**A nun should not ask a monk for permission to accuse him of an offense.*";
P_HTM[13435]="*kāritopi akārito;**If she does, it’s not actually done,*";
P_HTM[13436]="*kārentiyā āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13437]="*Na codetabbo;**A nun should not accuse a monk of an offense.*";
P_HTM[13438]="*coditopi acodito;**If she does, it’s not actually done,*";
P_HTM[13439]="*codentiyā āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and she commits an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[13440]="*Na sāretabbo;**A nun should not remind a monk of an offense.*";
P_HTM[13441]="*sāritopi asārito;**If she does, it’s not actually done,*";
P_HTM[13442]="*sārentiyā āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**and she commits an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[13443]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū bhikkhunīnaṃ uposathaṃ ṭhapenti, pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapenti, savacanīyaṃ karonti, anuvādaṃ paṭṭhapenti, okāsaṃ kārenti, codenti, sārenti.**At that time the monks canceled the nuns’ observance-day procedure and their invitation procedure; they spoke to them to initiate a legal process against them; they made accusations against them, asked them for permission to accuse them of offenses, accused them of offenses, and reminded them of offenses.*";
P_HTM[13444]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13445]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā bhikkhuniyā uposathaṃ ṭhapetuṃ;**“A monk may cancel the observance-day procedure of a nun.*";
P_HTM[13446]="*ṭhapitopi suṭṭhapito;**If he cancels it, it is properly canceled,*";
P_HTM[13447]="*ṭhapentassa anāpatti.**and there is no offense for him.*";
P_HTM[13448]="*Pavāraṇaṃ ṭhapetuṃ;**A monk may cancel the invitation procedure of a nun.*";
P_HTM[13449]="*ṭhapitāpi suṭṭhapitā;**If he cancels it, it is properly canceled,*";
P_HTM[13450]="*ṭhapentassa anāpatti.**and there is no offense for him.*";
P_HTM[13451]="*Savacanīyaṃ kātuṃ;**A monk may speak to a nun to initiate a legal process against her.*";
P_HTM[13452]="*katampi sukataṃ;**If he does, it is properly done,*";
P_HTM[13453]="*karontassa anāpatti.**and there is no offense for him.*";
P_HTM[13454]="*Anuvādaṃ paṭṭhapetuṃ;**A monk may make accusations against a nun.*";
P_HTM[13455]="*paṭṭhapitopi suppaṭṭhapito;**If he does, it is properly done,*";
P_HTM[13456]="*paṭṭhapentassa anāpatti.**and there is no offense for him.*";
P_HTM[13457]="*Okāsaṃ kāretuṃ;**A monk may ask a nun for permission to accuse her of an offense.*";
P_HTM[13458]="*kāritopi sukārito;**If he does, it is properly done,*";
P_HTM[13459]="*kārentassa anāpatti.**and there is no offense for him.*";
P_HTM[13460]="*Codetuṃ;**A monk may accuse a nun of an offense.*";
P_HTM[13461]="*coditāpi sucoditā;**If he does, it is properly done,*";
P_HTM[13462]="*codentassa anāpatti.**and there is no offense for him.*";
P_HTM[13463]="*Sāretuṃ;**A monk may remind a nun of an offense.*";
P_HTM[13464]="*sāritāpi susāritā;**If he does, it is properly done,*";
P_HTM[13465]="*sārentassa anāpattī”ti.**and there is no offense for him.”*";
P_HTM[13466]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo yānena yāyanti—**At that time the nuns from the group of six traveled in vehicles,*";
P_HTM[13467]="*itthiyuttenapi purisantarena, purisayuttenapi itthantarena.**sometimes pulled by women with men inside, at other times pulled by men with women inside.*";
P_HTM[13468]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti …pe…**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13469]="*seyyathāpi gaṅgāmahiyāyā”ti.**“It’s as if they’re at the Ganges festival.”*";
P_HTM[13470]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13471]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā yānena yāyitabbaṃ.**“A nun should not travel in a vehicle.*";
P_HTM[13472]="*Yā yāyeyya, yathādhammo kāretabbo”ti.**If she does, she should be dealt with according to the rule.”*";
P_HTM[13473]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā bhikkhunī gilānā hoti, na sakkoti padasā gantuṃ.**Soon afterwards there was a sick nun who was not able to go on foot.*";
P_HTM[13474]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13475]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānāya yānan”ti.**“I allow a vehicle for one who is sick.”*";
P_HTM[13476]="*Atha kho bhikkhunīnaṃ etadahosi—**The nuns thought,*";
P_HTM[13477]="*“itthiyuttaṃ nu kho, purisayuttaṃ nu kho”ti?**“A vehicle pulled by women or by men?”*";
P_HTM[13478]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13479]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, itthiyuttaṃ purisayuttaṃ hatthavaṭṭakan”ti.**“I allow a rickshaw pulled either by men or by women.”*";
P_HTM[13480]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarissā bhikkhuniyā yānugghātena bāḷhataraṃ aphāsu ahosi.**Soon afterwards a certain nun was even more uncomfortable when jolted around in a vehicle.*";
P_HTM[13481]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13482]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, sivikaṃ pāṭaṅkin”ti.**“I allow a palanquin and a litter.”*";
P_HTM[13483]="*Tena kho pana samayena aḍḍhakāsī gaṇikā bhikkhunīsu pabbajitā hoti.**At that time the courtesan Aḍḍhakāsī had gone forth with the nuns.*";
P_HTM[13484]="*Sā ca sāvatthiṃ gantukāmā hoti—**She wanted to go to Sāvatthī*";
P_HTM[13485]="*“bhagavato santike upasampajjissāmī”ti.**to get the full ordination in the presence of the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13486]="*Assosuṃ kho dhuttā—**Some scoundrels heard*";
P_HTM[13487]="*“aḍḍhakāsī kira gaṇikā sāvatthiṃ gantukāmā”ti.**about this*";
P_HTM[13488]="*Te magge pariyuṭṭhiṃsu.**and they infested the road.*";
P_HTM[13489]="*Assosi kho aḍḍhakāsī gaṇikā—**When Aḍḍhakāsī heard*";
P_HTM[13490]="*“dhuttā kira magge pariyuṭṭhitā”ti.**that scoundrels had infested the road,*";
P_HTM[13491]="*Bhagavato santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—**she sent a message to the Buddha, saying,*";
P_HTM[13492]="*“ahañhi upasampajjitukāmā;**“I want the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13493]="*kathaṃ nu kho mayā paṭipajjitabban”ti?**What should I do?”*";
P_HTM[13494]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[13495]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, dūtenapi upasampādetun”ti.**“I allow you to give the full ordination also by messenger.”*";
P_HTM[13496]="*Bhikkhudūtena upasampādenti.**They ordained with a monk as messenger.*";
P_HTM[13497]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13498]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhudūtena upasampādetabbā.**“You should not give the full ordination with a monk as messenger.*";
P_HTM[13499]="*Yo upasampādeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[13500]="*Sikkhamānadūtena upasampādenti …pe…**They ordained with a trainee nun as messenger …*";
P_HTM[13501]="*sāmaṇeradūtena upasampādenti …pe…**They ordained with a novice monk as messenger …*";
P_HTM[13502]="*sāmaṇeridūtena upasampādenti …pe…**They ordained with a novice nun as messenger …*";
P_HTM[13503]="*bālāya abyattāya dūtena upasampādenti.**They ordained with an ignorant and incompetent nun as messenger. The Buddha said,*";
P_HTM[13504]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bālāya abyattāya dūtena upasampādetabbā.**“You should not give the full ordination with an ignorant and incompetent nun as messenger.*";
P_HTM[13505]="*Yo upasampādeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13506]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya dūtena upasampādetunti.**You should give the full ordination with a capable and competent nun as messenger.*";
P_HTM[13507]="*Tāya dūtāya bhikkhuniyā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**That messenger nun should go to the Sangha, put her upper robe over one shoulder, bow down at the feet of the monks, squat on her heels, raise her joined palms, and say:*";
P_HTM[13508]="*‘itthannāmā, ayyā, itthannāmāya ayyāya upasampadāpekkhā.**‘Venerables, so-and-so is seeking the full ordination with Venerable so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13509]="*Ekatoupasampannā bhikkhunisaṅghe, visuddhā.**She is free from impediments and has been fully ordained on one side in the Sangha of nuns.*";
P_HTM[13510]="*Sā kenacideva antarāyena na āgacchati.**She hasn’t come because of an obstruction.*";
P_HTM[13511]="*Itthannāmā, ayyā, saṅghaṃ upasampadaṃ yācati.**She asks the Sangha for the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13512]="*Ullumpatu taṃ, ayyā, saṅgho anukampaṃ upādāya.**Please lift her up out of compassion.’*";
P_HTM[13513]="*Itthannāmā, ayyā, itthannāmāya ayyāya upasampadāpekkhā.**Venerables, so-and-so is seeking the full ordination with Venerable so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13514]="*Ekatoupasampannā bhikkhunisaṅghe, visuddhā.**She is free from impediments and has been fully ordained on one side in the Sangha of nuns.*";
P_HTM[13515]="*Sā kenacideva antarāyena na āgacchati.**She hasn’t come because of an obstruction.*";
P_HTM[13516]="*Dutiyampi, ayyā, itthannāmā saṅghaṃ upasampadaṃ yācati.**For the second time she asks the Sangha for the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13517]="*Ullumpatu taṃ, ayyā, saṅgho anukampaṃ upādāya.**Please lift her up out of compassion.’*";
P_HTM[13518]="*Itthannāmā, ayyā, itthannāmāya ayyāya upasampadāpekkhā.**Venerables, so-and-so is seeking the full ordination with Venerable so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13519]="*Ekatoupasampannā bhikkhunisaṅghe, visuddhā.**She is free from impediments and has been fully ordained on one side in the Sangha of nuns.*";
P_HTM[13520]="*Sā kenacideva antarāyena na āgacchati.**She hasn’t come because of an obstruction.*";
P_HTM[13521]="*Tatiyampi, ayyā, itthannāmā saṅghaṃ upasampadaṃ yācati.**For the third time she asks the Sangha for the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13522]="*Ullumpatu taṃ, ayyā, saṅgho anukampaṃ upādāyā’ti.**Please lift her up out of compassion.’*";
P_HTM[13523]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[13524]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13525]="*Itthannāmā itthannāmāya upasampadāpekkhā.**So-and-so is seeking the full ordination with Venerable so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13526]="*Ekatoupasampannā bhikkhunisaṅghe, visuddhā.**She is free from impediments and has been fully ordained on one side in the Sangha of nuns.*";
P_HTM[13527]="*Sā kenacideva antarāyena na āgacchati.**She hasn’t come because of an obstruction.*";
P_HTM[13528]="*Itthannāmā saṅghaṃ upasampadaṃ yācati itthannāmāya pavattiniyā.**So-and-so is asking the Sangha for the full ordination with so-and-so as her mentor.*";
P_HTM[13529]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmaṃ upasampādeyya itthannāmāya pavattiniyā.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should give her the full ordination with so-and-so as her mentor.*";
P_HTM[13530]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[13531]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13532]="*Itthannāmā itthannāmāya upasampadāpekkhā.**So-and-so is seeking the full ordination with Venerable so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13533]="*Ekatoupasampannā bhikkhunisaṅghe, visuddhā.**She is free from impediments and has been fully ordained on one side in the Sangha of nuns.*";
P_HTM[13534]="*Sā kenacideva antarāyena na āgacchati.**She hasn’t come because of an obstruction.*";
P_HTM[13535]="*Itthannāmā saṅghaṃ upasampadaṃ yācati itthannāmāya pavattiniyā.**So-and-so is asking the Sangha for the full ordination with so-and-so as her mentor.*";
P_HTM[13536]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ upasampādeti itthannāmāya pavattiniyā.**The Sangha gives her the full ordination with so-and-so as her mentor.*";
P_HTM[13537]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmāya upasampadā itthannāmāya pavattiniyā, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of giving so-and-so the full ordination with so-and-so as her mentor should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[13538]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[13539]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter. Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen. So-and-so is seeking the full ordination with Venerable so-and-so. She is free from impediments and has been fully ordained on one side in the Sangha of nuns. She hasn’t come because of an obstruction. So-and-so is asking the Sangha for the full ordination with so-and-so as her preceptor. The Sangha gives her the full ordination with so-and-so as her preceptor. Any monk who approves of giving so-and-so the full ordination with so-and-so as her preceptor should remain silent. Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[13540]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi.**For the third time I speak on this matter.*";
P_HTM[13541]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13542]="*Itthannāmā itthannāmāya upasampadāpekkhā.**So-and-so is seeking the full ordination with Venerable so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13543]="*Ekatoupasampannā bhikkhunisaṅghe, visuddhā.**She is free from impediments and has been fully ordained on one side in the Sangha of nuns.*";
P_HTM[13544]="*Sā kenacideva antarāyena na āgacchati.**She hasn’t come because of an obstruction.*";
P_HTM[13545]="*Itthannāmā saṅghaṃ upasampadaṃ yācati itthannāmāya pavattiniyā.**So-and-so is asking the Sangha for the full ordination with so-and-so as her mentor.*";
P_HTM[13546]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ upasampādeti itthannāmāya pavattiniyā.**The Sangha gives her the full ordination with so-and-so as her mentor.*";
P_HTM[13547]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmāya upasampadā itthannāmāya pavattiniyā, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of giving so-and-so the full ordination with so-and-so as her mentor should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[13548]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[13549]="*Upasampannā saṅghena itthannāmā itthannāmāya pavattiniyā.**The Sangha has given so-and-so the full ordination with so-and-so as her mentor.*";
P_HTM[13550]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[13551]="*Tāvadeva chāyā metabbā, utuppamāṇaṃ ācikkhitabbaṃ, divasabhāgo ācikkhitabbo, saṅgīti ācikkhitabbā, bhikkhuniyo vattabbā—**Straightaway the time should be noted and the date should be pointed out. These should be declared jointly to everyone.*";
P_HTM[13552]="*tassā tayo ca nissaye, aṭṭha ca akaraṇīyāni ācikkheyyāthā”ti.**The nuns should be told to point out the three supports and the eight things not to be done to the newly ordained nun.*";
P_HTM[13553]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo araññe viharanti.**At that time the nuns were living in the wilderness.*";
P_HTM[13554]="*Dhuttā dūsenti.**Scoundrels raped them.*";
P_HTM[13555]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ, ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13556]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā araññe vatthabbaṃ.**“A nun should not live in the wilderness.*";
P_HTM[13557]="*Yā vaseyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[13558]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarena upāsakena bhikkhunisaṅghassa uddosito dinno hoti.**On one occasion a lay follower gave a storehouse to the Sangha of nuns.*";
P_HTM[13559]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13560]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, uddositan”ti.**“I allow a storehouse.”*";
P_HTM[13561]="*Uddosito na sammati.**The storehouse was insufficient.*";
P_HTM[13562]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13563]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, upassayan”ti.**“I allow a dwelling place.”*";
P_HTM[13564]="*Upassayo na sammati.**The dwelling place was insufficient.*";
P_HTM[13565]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13566]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, navakamman”ti.**“I allow building work.”*";
P_HTM[13567]="*Navakammaṃ na sammati.**The building work was insufficient.*";
P_HTM[13568]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13569]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, puggalikampi kātun”ti.**“I allow you to build for individuals.”*";
P_HTM[13570]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā itthī sannisinnagabbhā bhikkhunīsu pabbajitā hoti.**At one time a pregnant woman went forth as a nun.*";
P_HTM[13571]="*Tassā pabbajitāya gabbho vuṭṭhāti.**After giving birth,*";
P_HTM[13572]="*Atha kho tassā bhikkhuniyā etadahosi—**she asked the nuns*";
P_HTM[13573]="*“kathaṃ nu kho mayā imasmiṃ dārake paṭipajjitabban”ti?**what she should do with the baby boy.*";
P_HTM[13574]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13575]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, posetuṃ, yāva so dārako viññutaṃ pāpuṇātī”ti.**“I allow you to rear him until he becomes self-reliant.”*";
P_HTM[13576]="*Atha kho tassā bhikkhuniyā etadahosi—**That nun thought,*";
P_HTM[13577]="*“mayā ca na labbhā ekikāya vatthuṃ, aññāya ca bhikkhuniyā na labbhā dārakena saha vatthuṃ, kathaṃ nu kho mayā paṭipajjitabban”ti?**“I’m not allowed to stay by myself and other nuns are not allowed to stay with a male child. What should I do?”*";
P_HTM[13578]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13579]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ekaṃ bhikkhuniṃ sammannitvā tassā bhikkhuniyā dutiyaṃ dātuṃ.**“The nuns should appoint one nun as a companion to that nun.*";
P_HTM[13580]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sammannitabbā.**And she should be appointed like this.*";
P_HTM[13581]="*Paṭhamaṃ bhikkhunī yācitabbā, yācitvā byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**First a nun should be asked, and then a capable and competent nun should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[13582]="*‘Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13583]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuniṃ sammanneyya itthannāmāya bhikkhuniyā dutiyaṃ.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should appoint nun so-and-so as a companion to nun so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13584]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[13585]="*Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13586]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuniṃ sammannati itthannāmāya bhikkhuniyā dutiyaṃ.**The Sangha appoints nun so-and-so as a companion to nun so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13587]="*Yassā ayyāya khamati itthannāmāya bhikkhuniyā sammuti itthannāmāya bhikkhuniyā dutiyāya, sā tuṇhassa;**Any nun who approves of appointing nun so-and-so as a companion to nun so-and-so should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[13588]="*yassā nakkhamati, sā bhāseyya.**Any nun who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[13589]="*Sammatā saṅghena itthannāmā bhikkhunī itthannāmāya bhikkhuniyā dutiyā.**The Sangha has appointed nun so-and-so as a companion to nun so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13590]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[13591]="*Atha kho tassā dutiyikāya bhikkhuniyā etadahosi—**That companion nun thought,*";
P_HTM[13592]="*“kathaṃ nu kho mayā imasmiṃ dārake paṭipajjitabban”ti?**“How should I act in regard to this boy?”*";
P_HTM[13593]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13594]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ṭhapetvā sāgāraṃ yathā aññasmiṃ purise paṭipajjanti evaṃ tasmiṃ dārake paṭipajjitun”ti.**“Apart from staying in the same dwelling, the companion nun should act toward him as she would toward any other male.”*";
P_HTM[13595]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā bhikkhunī garudhammaṃ ajjhāpannā hoti mānattacārinī.**On one occasion a nun who had committed a heavy offense was undertaking the trial period.*";
P_HTM[13596]="*Atha kho tassā bhikkhuniyā etadahosi—**She thought,*";
P_HTM[13597]="*“mayā ca na labbhā ekikāya vatthuṃ, aññāya ca bhikkhuniyā na labbhā saha mayā vatthuṃ, kathaṃ nu kho mayā paṭipajjitabban”ti?**“I’m not allowed to stay by myself and other nuns are not allowed to stay with me. What should I do?”*";
P_HTM[13598]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13599]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ekaṃ bhikkhuniṃ sammannitvā tassā bhikkhuniyā dutiyaṃ dātuṃ.**“You should appoint one nun as a companion to that nun.*";
P_HTM[13600]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sammannitabbā.**And she should be appointed like this.*";
P_HTM[13601]="*Paṭhamaṃ bhikkhunī yācitabbā, yācitvā byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**First a nun should be asked, and then a capable and competent nun should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[13602]="*‘Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13603]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuniṃ sammanneyya itthannāmāya bhikkhuniyā dutiyaṃ.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should appoint nun so-and-so as a companion to nun so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13604]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[13605]="*Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13606]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuniṃ sammannati itthannāmāya bhikkhuniyā dutiyaṃ.**The Sangha appoints nun so-and-so as a companion to nun so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13607]="*Yassā ayyāya khamati itthannāmāya bhikkhuniyā sammuti itthannāmāya bhikkhuniyā dutiyāya, sā tuṇhassa;**Any nun who approves of appointing nun so-and-so as a companion to nun so-and-so should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[13608]="*yassā nakkhamati, sā bhāseyya.**Any nun who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[13609]="*Sammatā saṅghena itthannāmā bhikkhunī itthannāmāya bhikkhuniyā dutiyā.**The Sangha has appointed nun so-and-so as a companion to nun so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[13610]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[13611]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā bhikkhunī sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya vibbhami.**On one occasion a nun verbally renounced the training and disrobed.*";
P_HTM[13612]="*Sā puna paccāgantvā bhikkhuniyo upasampadaṃ yāci.**Later she returned and asked the nuns for the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13613]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13614]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā sikkhāpaccakkhānaṃ;**“A nun can’t verbally renounce the training.*";
P_HTM[13615]="*yadeva sā vibbhantā tadeva sā abhikkhunī”ti.**When she disrobes, she is no longer a nun.”*";
P_HTM[13616]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā bhikkhunī sakāvāsā titthāyatanaṃ saṅkami.**On one occasion a nun joined another religious community while still wearing her robes.*";
P_HTM[13617]="*Sā puna paccāgantvā bhikkhuniyo upasampadaṃ yāci.**Later she returned and asked the nuns for the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13618]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13619]="*“Yā sā, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī sakāvāsā titthāyatanaṃ saṅkantā, sā āgatā na upasampādetabbā”ti.**“If a nun goes over to another religious community while still wearing her robes, then if she returns, she should not be given the full ordination again.”*";
P_HTM[13620]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo purisehi abhivādanaṃ, kesacchedanaṃ, nakhacchedanaṃ, vaṇappaṭikammaṃ, kukkuccāyantā na sādiyanti.**At that time the nuns, being afraid of wrongdoing, did not consent to men bowing down to them, or to men shaving their heads, cutting their nails, or treating their sores.*";
P_HTM[13621]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13622]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, sāditun”ti.**“I allow you to consent.”*";
P_HTM[13623]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo pallaṅkena nisīdanti paṇhisamphassaṃ sādiyantī.**At that time the nuns were sitting cross-legged, enjoying the touch of their heals.*";
P_HTM[13624]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13625]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā pallaṅkena nisīditabbaṃ.**“A nun should not sit cross-legged.*";
P_HTM[13626]="*Yā nisīdeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[13627]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā bhikkhunī gilānā hoti.**On one occasion there was a sick nun*";
P_HTM[13628]="*Tassā vinā pallaṅkena na phāsu hoti.**who was not comfortable without sitting cross-legged.*";
P_HTM[13629]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13630]="*“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā aḍḍhapallaṅkan”ti.**“I allow a nun to sit semi-cross-legged.”*";
P_HTM[13631]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo vaccakuṭiyā vaccaṃ karonti.**At that time the nuns were defecating in a restroom.*";
P_HTM[13632]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo tattheva gabbhaṃ pātenti.**And the nuns from the group of six performed abortions there.*";
P_HTM[13633]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13634]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā vaccakuṭiyā vacco kātabbo.**“A nun should not defecate in a restroom.*";
P_HTM[13635]="*Yā kareyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13636]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, heṭṭhā vivaṭe uparipaṭicchanne vaccaṃ kātun”ti.**I allow nuns to defecate in a place that is open underneath but concealed on top.”*";
P_HTM[13637]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo cuṇṇena nahāyanti.**At that time the nuns were bathing with bath powder.*";
P_HTM[13638]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti …pe…**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13639]="*seyyathāpi gihinī kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[13640]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13641]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā cuṇṇena nahāyitabbaṃ.**“A nun should not bathe with bath powder.*";
P_HTM[13642]="*Yā nahāyeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13643]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kukkusaṃ mattikan”ti.**I allow bran and clay.”*";
P_HTM[13644]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo vāsitakāya mattikāya nahāyanti.**At that time the nuns were bathing with scented clay.*";
P_HTM[13645]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti …pe…**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13646]="*seyyathāpi gihinī kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[13647]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13648]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā vāsitakāya mattikāya nahāyitabbaṃ.**“A nun should not bathe with scented clay.*";
P_HTM[13649]="*Yā nahāyeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13650]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pakatimattikan”ti.**I allow ordinary clay.”*";
P_HTM[13651]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo jantāghare nahāyantiyo kolāhalaṃ akaṃsu.**On one occasion when the nuns were bathing in a sauna, they made a racket.*";
P_HTM[13652]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13653]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā jantāghare nahāyitabbaṃ.**“A nun should not bathe in a sauna.*";
P_HTM[13654]="*Yā nahāyeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[13655]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo paṭisote nahāyanti dhārāsamphassaṃ sādiyantī.**On one occasion the nuns were bathing against the stream, consenting to the touch of the current.*";
P_HTM[13656]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13657]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā paṭisote nahāyitabbaṃ.**“A nun should not bathe against the stream.*";
P_HTM[13658]="*Yā nahāyeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[13659]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo atitthe nahāyanti.**On one occasion the nuns bathed away from a ford.*";
P_HTM[13660]="*Dhuttā dūsenti.**Scoundrels raped them.*";
P_HTM[13661]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13662]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā atitthe nahāyitabbaṃ.**“A nun should not bathe away from a ford.*";
P_HTM[13663]="*Yā nahāyeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[13664]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo purisatitthe nahāyanti.**On one occasion the nuns bathed at a ford for men.*";
P_HTM[13665]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti …pe…**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13666]="*seyyathāpi gihinī kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[13667]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13668]="*“Na, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyā purisatitthe nahāyitabbaṃ.**“A nun should not bathe at a ford for men.*";
P_HTM[13669]="*Yā nahāyeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13670]="*Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, mahilātitthe nahāyitun”ti.**A nun should bathe at a ford for women.”*";
P_HTM[13671]="*Tatiyabhāṇavāro niṭṭhito.**The third section for recitation is finished.*";
P_HTM[13672]="*Bhikkhunikkhandhako dasamo.**The tenth chapter on nuns is finished.*";
P_HTM[13673]="*Imasmiṃ khandhake vatthū ekasataṃ.**In this chapter there are one hundred topics.*";
P_HTM[13674]="*Tassuddānaṃ* **";
P_HTM[13675]="*Pabbajjaṃ gotamī yāci,* **";
P_HTM[13676]="*nānuññāsi tathāgato;* **";
P_HTM[13677]="*Kapilavatthu vesāliṃ,* **";
P_HTM[13678]="*agamāsi vināyako.* **";
P_HTM[13679]="*Rajokiṇṇena koṭṭhake,* **";
P_HTM[13680]="*ānandassa pavedayi;* **";
P_HTM[13681]="*Bhabboti nayato yāci,* **";
P_HTM[13682]="*mātāti posikāti ca.* **";
P_HTM[13683]="*Vassasataṃ tadahu ca,* **";
P_HTM[13684]="*abhikkhupaccāsīsanā;* **";
P_HTM[13685]="*Pavāraṇā garudhammā,* **";
P_HTM[13686]="*dve vassā anakkosanā.* **";
P_HTM[13687]="*Ovaṭo ca aṭṭha dhammā,* **";
P_HTM[13688]="*yāvajīvānuvattanā;* **";
P_HTM[13689]="*Garudhammapaṭiggāho,* **";
P_HTM[13690]="*sāvassā upasampadā.* **";
P_HTM[13691]="*Vassasahassaṃ pañceva,* **";
P_HTM[13692]="*kumbhathenakasetaṭṭi;* **";
P_HTM[13693]="*Mañjiṭṭhikaupamāhi,* **";
P_HTM[13694]="*evaṃ saddhammahiṃsanā.* **";
P_HTM[13695]="*Āḷiṃ bandheyya pāeva,* **";
P_HTM[13696]="*puna saddhammasaṇṭhiti;* **";
P_HTM[13697]="*Upasampādetuṃ ayyā,* **";
P_HTM[13698]="*yathāvuḍḍhābhivādanā.* **";
P_HTM[13699]="*Na karissanti kimeva,* **";
P_HTM[13700]="*sādhāraṇāsādhāraṇaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[13701]="*Ovādaṃ pātimokkhañca,* **";
P_HTM[13702]="*kena nu kho upassayaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[13703]="*Na jānanti ca ācikkhi,* **";
P_HTM[13704]="*na karonti ca bhikkhuhi;* **";
P_HTM[13705]="*Paṭiggahetuṃ bhikkhūhi,* **";
P_HTM[13706]="*bhikkhunīhi paṭiggaho.* **";
P_HTM[13707]="*Ācikkhi kammaṃ bhikkhūhi,* **";
P_HTM[13708]="*ujjhāyanti bhikkhunīhi vā;* **";
P_HTM[13709]="*Ācikkhituṃ bhaṇḍanañca,* **";
P_HTM[13710]="*ropetvā uppalāya ca.* **";
P_HTM[13711]="*Sāvatthiyā kaddamoda,* **";
P_HTM[13712]="*avandi kāya ūru ca;* **";
P_HTM[13713]="*Aṅgajātañca obhāsaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[13714]="*sampayojenti vaggikā.* **";
P_HTM[13715]="*Avandiyo daṇḍakammaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[13716]="*bhikkhuniyo tathā puna;* **";
P_HTM[13717]="*Āvaraṇañca ovādaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[13718]="*kappati nu kho pakkami.* **";
P_HTM[13719]="*Bālā vatthuvinicchayā,* **";
P_HTM[13720]="*ovādaṃ saṅgho pañcahi;* **";
P_HTM[13721]="*Duve tisso na gaṇhanti,* **";
P_HTM[13722]="*bālā gilānagamikaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[13723]="*Āraññiko nārocenti,* **";
P_HTM[13724]="*na paccāgacchanti ca;* **";
P_HTM[13725]="*Dīghaṃ vilīvacammañca,* **";
P_HTM[13726]="*dussā ca veṇivaṭṭi ca;* **";
P_HTM[13727]="*Coḷaveṇi ca vaṭṭi ca,* **";
P_HTM[13728]="*suttaveṇi ca vaṭṭikā.* **";
P_HTM[13729]="*Aṭṭhillaṃ gohanukena,* **";
P_HTM[13730]="*hatthakocchaṃ pādaṃ tathā;* **";
P_HTM[13731]="*Ūruṃ mukhaṃ dantamaṃsaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[13732]="*ālimpomaddacuṇṇanā.* **";
P_HTM[13733]="*Lañchenti aṅgarāgañca,* **";
P_HTM[13734]="*mukharāgaṃ tathā duve;* **";
P_HTM[13735]="*Avaṅgaṃ visesoloko,* **";
P_HTM[13736]="*sālokena naccena ca.* **";
P_HTM[13737]="*Vesī pānāgāraṃ sūnaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[13738]="*āpaṇaṃ vaḍḍhi vaṇijjā;* **";
P_HTM[13739]="*Dāsaṃ dāsiṃ kammakaraṃ,* **";
P_HTM[13740]="*kammakāriṃ upaṭṭhayyuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[13741]="*Tiracchānaharītaki,* **";
P_HTM[13742]="*sandhārayanti namatakaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[13743]="*Nīlaṃ pītaṃ lohitakaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[13744]="*mañjiṭṭhakaṇhacīvarā.* **";
P_HTM[13745]="*Mahāraṅgamahānāma-* **";
P_HTM[13746]="*acchinnā dīghameva ca;* **";
P_HTM[13747]="*Pupphaphalakañcukañca,* **";
P_HTM[13748]="*tirīṭakañca dhārayuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[13749]="*Bhikkhunī sikkhamānāya,* **";
P_HTM[13750]="*sāmaṇerāya accaye;* **";
P_HTM[13751]="*Niyyādite parikkhāre,* **";
P_HTM[13752]="*bhikkhuniyova issarā.* **";
P_HTM[13753]="*Bhikkhussa sāmaṇerassa,* **";
P_HTM[13754]="*upāsakassupāsikā;* **";
P_HTM[13755]="*Aññesañca parikkhāre,* **";
P_HTM[13756]="*niyyāte bhikkhuissarā.* **";
P_HTM[13757]="*Mallī gabbhaṃ pattamūlaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[13758]="*byañjanaṃ āmisena ca;* **";
P_HTM[13759]="*Ussannañca bāḷhataraṃ,* **";
P_HTM[13760]="*sannidhikatamāmisaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[13761]="*Bhikkhūnaṃ yādisaṃ bhoṭṭhaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[13762]="*Bhikkhunīnaṃ tathā kare;* **";
P_HTM[13763]="*Senāsanaṃ utuniyo,* **";
P_HTM[13764]="*Makkhīyati paṭāṇi ca.* **";
P_HTM[13765]="*Chijjanti sabbakālañca,* **";
P_HTM[13766]="*animittāpi dissare;* **";
P_HTM[13767]="*Nimittā lohitā ceva,* **";
P_HTM[13768]="*tatheva dhuvalohitā.* **";
P_HTM[13769]="*Dhuvacoḷapaggharantī,* **";
P_HTM[13770]="*sikharaṇitthipaṇḍakā;* **";
P_HTM[13771]="*Vepurisī ca sambhinnā,* **";
P_HTM[13772]="*ubhatobyañjanāpi ca.* **";
P_HTM[13773]="*Animittādito katvā,* **";
P_HTM[13774]="*yāva ubhatobyañjanā;* **";
P_HTM[13775]="*Etaṃ peyyālato heṭṭhā,* **";
P_HTM[13776]="*kuṭṭhaṃ gaṇḍo kilāso ca.* **";
P_HTM[13777]="*Sosāpamāro mānusī,* **";
P_HTM[13778]="*itthīsi bhujissāsi ca;* **";
P_HTM[13779]="*Aṇaṇā na rājabhaṭī,* **";
P_HTM[13780]="*anuññātā ca vīsati.* **";
P_HTM[13781]="*Paripuṇṇā ca kiṃnāmā,* **";
P_HTM[13782]="*kānāmā te pavattinī;* **";
P_HTM[13783]="*Catuvīsantarāyānaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[13784]="*pucchitvā upasampadā.* **";
P_HTM[13785]="*Vitthāyanti ananusiṭṭhā,* **";
P_HTM[13786]="*saṅghamajjhe tatheva ca;* **";
P_HTM[13787]="*Upajjhāgāha saṅghāṭi,* **";
P_HTM[13788]="*uttarantaravāsako.* **";
P_HTM[13789]="*Saṅkaccudakasāṭi ca,* **";
P_HTM[13790]="*ācikkhitvāna pesaye;* **";
P_HTM[13791]="*Bālā asammatekato,* **";
P_HTM[13792]="*yāce pucchantarāyikā.* **";
P_HTM[13793]="*Ekatoupasampannā,* **";
P_HTM[13794]="*bhikkhusaṅghe tathā puna;* **";
P_HTM[13795]="*Chāyā utu divasā ca,* **";
P_HTM[13796]="*saṅgīti tayo nissaye.* **";
P_HTM[13797]="*Aṭṭha akaraṇīyāni,* **";
P_HTM[13798]="*kālaṃ sabbattha aṭṭheva;* **";
P_HTM[13799]="*Na pavārenti bhikkhunī,* **";
P_HTM[13800]="*bhikkhusaṅghaṃ tatheva ca.* **";
P_HTM[13801]="*Kolāhalaṃ purebhattaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[13802]="*vikāle ca kolāhalaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[13803]="*Uposathaṃ pavāraṇaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[13804]="*savacanīyānuvādanaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[13805]="*Okāsaṃ code sārenti,* **";
P_HTM[13806]="*paṭikkhittaṃ mahesinā;* **";
P_HTM[13807]="*Tatheva bhikkhu bhikkhunī,* **";
P_HTM[13808]="*anuññātaṃ mahesinā.* **";
P_HTM[13809]="*Yānaṃ gilānayuttañca,* **";
P_HTM[13810]="*yānugghātaḍḍhakāsikā;* **";
P_HTM[13811]="*Bhikkhu sikkhā sāmaṇera,* **";
P_HTM[13812]="*sāmaṇerī ca bālāya.* **";
P_HTM[13813]="*Araññe upāsakena,* **";
P_HTM[13814]="*uddosito upassayaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[13815]="*Na sammati navakammaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[13816]="*nisinnagabbhaekikā.* **";
P_HTM[13817]="*Sāgārañca garudhammaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[13818]="*paccakkhāya ca saṅkami;* **";
P_HTM[13819]="*Abhivādanakesā ca,* **";
P_HTM[13820]="*nakhā ca vaṇakammanā.* **";
P_HTM[13821]="*Pallaṅkena gilānā ca,* **";
P_HTM[13822]="*vaccaṃ cuṇṇena vāsitaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[13823]="*Jantāghare paṭisote,* **";
P_HTM[13824]="*atitthe purisena ca.* **";
P_HTM[13825]="*Mahāgotamī āyāci,**Mahāgotamī asked,*";
P_HTM[13826]="*ānando cāpi yoniso;**And so did Ānanda wisely.*";
P_HTM[13827]="*Parisā catasso honti,**There are four assemblies,*";
P_HTM[13828]="*pabbajjā jinasāsane.**Gone forth in the instruction of the Conqueror.*";
P_HTM[13829]="*Saṃvegajananatthāya,**For the purpose of seeing the urgency,*";
P_HTM[13830]="*saddhammassa ca vuddhiyā;**For the purpose of growth in the true Teaching,*";
P_HTM[13831]="*Āturassāva bhesajjaṃ,**Like medicine for the sick,*";
P_HTM[13832]="*evaṃ buddhena desitaṃ.**So it was taught by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13833]="*Evaṃ vinītā saddhamme,**Thus trained in the true Teaching,*";
P_HTM[13834]="*mātugāmāpi itarā;**Women and others too,*";
P_HTM[13835]="*Yāyanti accutaṃ ṭhānaṃ,**Go to that which is free from death,*";
P_HTM[13836]="*yattha gantvā na socareti.**Where there is no sorrow.*";
P_HTM[13837]="*Bhikkhunikkhandhako niṭṭhito.**The chapter on nuns is finished.*";
P_HTM[13838]="*11. Pañcasatikakkhandhaka **11.  The chapter on the group of five hundred *";
P_HTM[13839]="*1. Saṅgītinidāna**1. The origin account of the communal recitation*";
P_HTM[13840]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo bhikkhū āmantesi—**Then Venerable Mahākassapa addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[13841]="*“ekamidāhaṃ, āvuso, samayaṃ pāvāya kusināraṃ addhānamaggappaṭipanno mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi.**“On one occasion I was traveling from Pāvā to Kusināra with a large sangha of five hundred monks.*";
P_HTM[13842]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, āvuso, maggā okkamma aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle nisīdiṃ.**And I left the road and sat down at the foot of a tree.*";
P_HTM[13843]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro ājīvako kusinārāya mandāravapupphaṃ gahetvā pāvaṃ addhānamaggappaṭipanno hoti.**Just then a follower of the Ājīvakas was traveling toward Pāvā on the same road, holding a coral-tree flower that he had picked up in Kusināra.*";
P_HTM[13844]="*Addasaṃ kho ahaṃ, āvuso, taṃ ājīvakaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**When I saw him coming,*";
P_HTM[13845]="*Disvāna taṃ ājīvakaṃ etadavocaṃ—**I asked him,*";
P_HTM[13846]="*‘apāvuso, amhākaṃ satthāraṃ jānāsī’ti?**‘Do you know anything about our Teacher?’*";
P_HTM[13847]="*‘Āmāvuso, jānāmi.**‘I do.*";
P_HTM[13848]="*Ajja sattāhaparinibbuto samaṇo gotamo.**Today it’s seven days since the ascetic Gotama attained final extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[13849]="*Tato me idaṃ mandāravapupphaṃ gahitan’ti.**That’s why I carry this coral-tree flower.’*";
P_HTM[13850]="*Tatrāvuso, ye te bhikkhū avītarāgā appekacce bāhā paggayha kandanti, chinnapātaṃ papatanti, āvaṭṭanti, vivaṭṭanti—**Some of the monks there who were not yet free from desire threw up their arms and cried, collapsed on the ground, and rolled back and forth, lamenting,*";
P_HTM[13851]="*atikhippaṃ bhagavā parinibbuto, atikhippaṃ sugato parinibbuto, atikhippaṃ cakkhuṃ loke antarahitanti.**‘The Buddha, the Happy One, has attained final extinguishment too soon; too soon has the eye of the world been put out.’*";
P_HTM[13852]="*Ye pana te bhikkhū vītarāgā te satā sampajānā adhivāsenti—**But the monks there who were free from desire bore it patiently with mindfulness and full awareness, saying,*";
P_HTM[13853]="*aniccā saṅkhārā, taṃ kutettha labbhāti.**‘All phenomena are impermanent. How could it be any different?’*";
P_HTM[13854]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, āvuso, te bhikkhū etadavocaṃ—**I said,*";
P_HTM[13855]="*‘alaṃ, āvuso, mā socittha;**‘Please stop grieving,*";
P_HTM[13856]="*mā paridevittha.**stop lamenting.*";
P_HTM[13857]="*Nanvetaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā paṭikacceva akkhātaṃ—**Didn’t the Buddha warn us*";
P_HTM[13858]="*sabbeheva piyehi manāpehi nānābhāvo vinābhāvo aññathābhāvo.**that we must be separated from everyone and everything dear and agreeable to us?*";
P_HTM[13859]="*Taṃ kutettha āvuso labbhā, yaṃ taṃ jātaṃ bhūtaṃ saṅkhataṃ palokadhammaṃ, taṃ vata mā palujjīti—**How could that which is born, become, made up, and of a nature to fall apart, not fall apart?*";
P_HTM[13860]="*netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjatī’ti.**That’s impossible.’*";
P_HTM[13861]="*Tena kho panāvuso, samayena subhaddo nāma vuḍḍhapabbajito tassaṃ parisāyaṃ nisinno hoti.**On that occasion a monk called Subhadda, who had gone forth when old, was part of that group.*";
P_HTM[13862]="*Atha kho, āvuso, subhaddo vuḍḍhapabbajito te bhikkhū etadavoca—**He said to the monks,*";
P_HTM[13863]="*‘alaṃ, āvuso, mā socittha;**‘Please stop grieving,*";
P_HTM[13864]="*mā paridevittha.**stop lamenting.*";
P_HTM[13865]="*Sumuttā mayaṃ tena mahāsamaṇena;**It’s good that we are freed from that great ascetic.*";
P_HTM[13866]="*upaddutā ca mayaṃ homa—**We were oppressed,*";
P_HTM[13867]="*idaṃ vo kappati, idaṃ vo na kappatīti.**always being told what’s allowable and what isn’t.*";
P_HTM[13868]="*Idāni pana mayaṃ yaṃ icchissāma taṃ karissāma, yaṃ na icchissāma na taṃ karissāmā’ti.**Now we can do what we like and not do what we don’t like.’*";
P_HTM[13869]="*Handa mayaṃ, āvuso, dhammañca vinayañca saṅgāyāma.**So then, let’s recite the Teaching and the Monastic Law together—*";
P_HTM[13870]="*Pure adhammo dippati, dhammo paṭibāhiyyati;**before what is contrary to the Teaching shines forth and the Teaching is obstructed;*";
P_HTM[13871]="*pure avinayo dippati vinayo paṭibāhiyyati;**before what is contrary to the Monastic Law shines forth and the Monastic Law is obstructed;*";
P_HTM[13872]="*pure adhammavādino balavanto honti, dhammavādino dubbalā honti;**before those who speak contrary to the Teaching become strong and those who speak in accordance with it become weak;*";
P_HTM[13873]="*pure avinayavādino balavanto honti, vinayavādino dubbalā hontī”ti.**before those who speak contrary to the Monastic Law become strong and those who speak in accordance with it become weak.”*";
P_HTM[13874]="*“Tena hi, bhante, thero bhikkhū uccinatū”ti.**“Well then, Venerable, please select the monks.”*";
P_HTM[13875]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo ekenūnapañcaarahantasatāni uccini.**Mahākassapa then selected four hundred and ninety-nine perfected ones.*";
P_HTM[13876]="*Bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ mahākassapaṃ etadavocuṃ—**The monks said to him,*";
P_HTM[13877]="*“ayaṃ, bhante, āyasmā ānando kiñcāpi sekkho, abhabbo chandā dosā mohā bhayā agatiṃ gantuṃ.**“There is Venerable Ānanda who, although still a trainee, is incapable of acting out of desire, ill will, confusion, or fear.*";
P_HTM[13878]="*Bahu ca anena bhagavato santike dhammo ca vinayo ca pariyatto.**He’s learned many teachings and much Monastic Law in the presence of the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[13879]="*Tena hi, bhante, thero āyasmantampi ānandaṃ uccinatū”ti.**Please invite him as well.”*";
P_HTM[13880]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo āyasmantampi ānandaṃ uccini.**And he did.*";
P_HTM[13881]="*Atha kho therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The senior monks thought,*";
P_HTM[13882]="*“kattha nu kho mayaṃ dhammañca vinayañca saṅgāyeyyāmā”ti?**“Where should we recite the Teaching and the Monastic Law together?”*";
P_HTM[13883]="*Atha kho therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**And it occurred to them,*";
P_HTM[13884]="*“rājagahaṃ kho mahāgocaraṃ pahūtasenāsanaṃ, yannūna mayaṃ rājagahe vassaṃ vasantā dhammañca vinayañca saṅgāyeyyāma.**“Rājagaha has much almsfood and many dwellings. Let’s spend the rainy season at Rājagaha and recite the Teaching and the Monastic Law together there.*";
P_HTM[13885]="*Na aññe bhikkhū rājagahe vassaṃ upagaccheyyun”ti.**No other monk should enter the rainy-season residence at Rājagaha.”*";
P_HTM[13886]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo saṅghaṃ ñāpesi—**And Venerable Mahākassapa informed the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[13887]="*“Suṇātu me, āvuso, saṅgho.**“Please, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13888]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho imāni pañca bhikkhusatāni sammanneyya—**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should appoint these five hundred monks*";
P_HTM[13889]="*rājagahe vassaṃ vasantāni dhammañca vinayañca saṅgāyituṃ, na aññehi bhikkhūhi rājagahe vassaṃ vasitabbanti.**to spend the rainy season at Rājagaha and to recite the Teaching and the Monastic Law together there. No other monk should enter the rainy-season residence at Rājagaha.*";
P_HTM[13890]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[13891]="*Suṇātu me, āvuso, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13892]="*Imāni pañca bhikkhusatāni sammannati—**The Sangha appoints these five hundred monks*";
P_HTM[13893]="*rājagahe vassaṃ vasantāni dhammañca vinayañca saṅgāyituṃ, na aññehi bhikkhūhi rājagahe vassaṃ vasitabbanti.**to spend the rainy season at Rājagaha and to recite the Teaching and the Monastic Law together there. No other monk should enter the rainy-season residence at Rājagaha.*";
P_HTM[13894]="*Yassāyasmato khamati imesaṃ pañcannaṃ bhikkhusatānaṃ sammuti—**Any monk who approves*";
P_HTM[13895]="*rājagahe vassaṃ vasantānaṃ dhammañca vinayañca saṅgāyituṃ, na aññehi bhikkhūhi rājagahe vassaṃ vasitabbanti—**of this*";
P_HTM[13896]="*so tuṇhassa;**should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[13897]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[13898]="*Sammatāni saṅghena imāni pañca bhikkhusatāni rājagahe vassaṃ vasantāni dhammañca vinayañca saṅgāyituṃ, na aññehi bhikkhūhi rājagahe vassaṃ vasitabbanti.**The Sangha has appointed these five hundred monks to spend the rainy season at Rājagaha and to recite the Teaching and the Monastic Law together there. No other monk should enter the rainy-season residence at Rājagaha.*";
P_HTM[13899]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.”*";
P_HTM[13900]="*Atha kho therā bhikkhū rājagahaṃ agamaṃsu dhammañca vinayañca saṅgāyituṃ.**The senior monks then went to Rājagaha to recite the Teaching and the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[13901]="*Atha kho therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**They thought,*";
P_HTM[13902]="*“bhagavatā kho, āvuso, khaṇḍaphullapaṭisaṅkharaṇaṃ vaṇṇitaṃ.**“The Buddha has praised repairing what’s defective and broken.*";
P_HTM[13903]="*Handa mayaṃ, āvuso, paṭhamaṃ māsaṃ khaṇḍaphullaṃ paṭisaṅkharoma;**Well then, let’s spend the first month doing repairs,*";
P_HTM[13904]="*majjhimaṃ māsaṃ sannipatitvā dhammañca vinayañca saṅgāyissāmā”ti.**and then gather for the middle month to recite the Teaching and the Monastic Law.”*";
P_HTM[13905]="*Atha kho therā bhikkhū paṭhamaṃ māsaṃ khaṇḍaphullaṃ paṭisaṅkhariṃsu.**They then spent the first month doing repairs.*";
P_HTM[13906]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando—**Venerable Ānanda thought,*";
P_HTM[13907]="*“sve sannipāto na kho metaṃ patirūpaṃ, yohaṃ sekkho samāno sannipātaṃ gaccheyyan”ti—**It would not be proper for me to go to the assembly tomorrow if I’m still a trainee.”*";
P_HTM[13908]="*bahudeva rattiṃ kāyagatāya satiyā vītināmetvā rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ “nipajjissāmī”ti kāyaṃ āvajjesi.**And after spending most of the night with mindfulness directed to the body, early in the morning he bent over to lie down.*";
P_HTM[13909]="*Appattañca sīsaṃ bibbohanaṃ, bhūmito ca pādā muttā.**In the interval between his feet coming off the ground and his head hitting the pillow*";
P_HTM[13910]="*Etasmiṃ antare anupādāya āsavehi cittaṃ vimucci.**his mind was freed from the corruptions through letting go.*";
P_HTM[13911]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando arahā samāno sannipātaṃ agamāsi.**And Venerable Ānanda went to the assembly as a perfected one.*";
P_HTM[13912]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo saṅghaṃ ñāpesi—**Venerable Mahākassapa informed the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[13913]="*“Suṇātu me, āvuso, saṅgho.**“Please, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13914]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, ahaṃ upāliṃ vinayaṃ puccheyyan”ti.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, I will ask Upāli about the Monastic Law.”*";
P_HTM[13915]="*Āyasmā upāli saṅghaṃ ñāpesi—**Venerable Upāli informed the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[13916]="*“Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**“Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13917]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, ahaṃ āyasmatā mahākassapena vinayaṃ puṭṭho vissajjeyyan”ti.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, I will reply when asked by Venerable Mahākassapa about the Monastic Law.”*";
P_HTM[13918]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo āyasmantaṃ upāliṃ etadavoca—**And Mahākassapa asked Upāli,*";
P_HTM[13919]="*“paṭhamaṃ, āvuso upāli, pārājikaṃ kattha paññattan”ti?**“Where was the first offense entailing expulsion laid down?”*";
P_HTM[13920]="*“Vesāliyaṃ, bhante”ti.**“At Vesālī.”*";
P_HTM[13921]="*“Kaṃ ārabbhā”ti?**“Who is it about?”*";
P_HTM[13922]="*“Sudinnaṃ kalandaputtaṃ ārabbhā”ti.**“Sudinna the Kalandian.”*";
P_HTM[13923]="*“Kismiṃ vatthusmin”ti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[13924]="*“Methunadhamme”ti.**“Sexual intercourse.”*";
P_HTM[13925]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo āyasmantaṃ upāliṃ paṭhamassa pārājikassa vatthumpi pucchi, nidānampi pucchi, puggalampi pucchi, paññattimpi pucchi, anupaññattimpi pucchi, āpattimpi pucchi, anāpattimpi pucchi.**Mahākassapa asked Upāli about the topic of the first offense entailing expulsion, about the origin story, about the person, about the rule, about the additions to the rule, about the offense, and about the non-offenses.*";
P_HTM[13926]="*“Dutiyaṃ panāvuso upāli, pārājikaṃ kattha paññattan”ti?**“And where was the second offense entailing expulsion laid down?”*";
P_HTM[13927]="*“Rājagahe, bhante”ti.**“At Rājagaha.”*";
P_HTM[13928]="*“Kaṃ ārabbhā”ti?**“Who is it about?”*";
P_HTM[13929]="*“Dhaniyaṃ kumbhakāraputtaṃ ārabbhā”ti.**“Dhaniya the potter.”*";
P_HTM[13930]="*“Kismiṃ vatthusmin”ti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[13931]="*“Adinnādāne”ti.**“Stealing.”*";
P_HTM[13932]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo āyasmantaṃ upāliṃ dutiyassa pārājikassa vatthumpi pucchi, nidānampi pucchi, puggalampi pucchi, paññattimpi pucchi, anupaññattimpi pucchi, āpattimpi pucchi, anāpattimpi pucchi.**Mahākassapa asked Upāli about the topic of the second offense entailing expulsion, about the origin story, about the person, about the rule, about the additions to the rule, about the offense, and about the non-offenses.*";
P_HTM[13933]="*“Tatiyaṃ panāvuso upāli, pārājikaṃ kattha paññattan”ti?**“And where was the third offense entailing expulsion laid down?”*";
P_HTM[13934]="*“Vesāliyaṃ, bhante”ti.**“At Vesālī.”*";
P_HTM[13935]="*“Kaṃ ārabbhā”ti?**“Who is it about?”*";
P_HTM[13936]="*“Sambahule bhikkhū ārabbhā”ti.**“A number of monks.”*";
P_HTM[13937]="*“Kismiṃ vatthusmin”ti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[13938]="*“Manussaviggahe”ti.**“Human beings.”*";
P_HTM[13939]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo āyasmantaṃ upāliṃ tatiyassa pārājikassa vatthumpi pucchi, nidānampi pucchi, puggalampi pucchi, paññattimpi pucchi, anupaññattimpi pucchi, āpattimpi pucchi, anāpattimpi pucchi.**Mahākassapa asked Upāli about the topic of the third offense entailing expulsion, about the origin story, about the person, about the rule, about the additions to the rule, about the offense, and about the non-offenses.*";
P_HTM[13940]="*“Catutthaṃ panāvuso upāli, pārājikaṃ kattha paññattan”ti?**“And where was the fourth offense entailing expulsion laid down?”*";
P_HTM[13941]="*“Vesāliyaṃ, bhante”ti.**“At Vesālī.”*";
P_HTM[13942]="*“Kaṃ ārabbhā”ti?**“Who is it about?”*";
P_HTM[13943]="*“Vaggumudātīriye bhikkhū ārabbhā”ti.**“The monks from the banks of the Vaggumudā.”*";
P_HTM[13944]="*“Kismiṃ vatthusmin”ti?**“What is it about?”*";
P_HTM[13945]="*“Uttarimanussadhamme”ti.**“Superhuman qualities.”*";
P_HTM[13946]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo āyasmantaṃ upāliṃ catutthassa pārājikassa vatthumpi pucchi, nidānampi pucchi, puggalampi pucchi, paññattimpi pucchi, anupaññattimpi pucchi, āpattimpi pucchi, anāpattimpi pucchi.**Mahākassapa asked Upāli about the topic of the fourth offense entailing expulsion, about the origin story, about the person, about the rule, about the additions to the rule, about the offense, and about the non-offenses.*";
P_HTM[13947]="*Eteneva upāyena ubhatovibhaṅge pucchi.**In this way he asked about the analyses of both Monastic Codes.*";
P_HTM[13948]="*Puṭṭho puṭṭho āyasmā upāli vissajjesi.**And Upāli was able to reply to every question.*";
P_HTM[13949]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo saṅghaṃ ñāpesi—**Venerable Mahākassapa informed the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[13950]="*“Suṇātu me, āvuso, saṅgho.**“Please, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13951]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, ahaṃ ānandaṃ dhammaṃ puccheyyan”ti.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, I will ask Ānanda about the Teaching.”*";
P_HTM[13952]="*Āyasmā ānando saṅghaṃ ñāpesi—**Venerable Ānanda informed the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[13953]="*“Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**“Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13954]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, ahaṃ āyasmatā mahākassapena dhammaṃ puṭṭho vissajjeyyan”ti.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, I will reply when asked by Venerable Mahākassapa about the Teaching.”*";
P_HTM[13955]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca—**And Mahākassapa asked Ānanda,*";
P_HTM[13956]="*“brahmajālaṃ, āvuso ānanda, kattha bhāsitan”ti?**“Where was the Prime Net spoken?”*";
P_HTM[13957]="*“Antarā ca, bhante, rājagahaṃ antarā ca nāḷandaṃ rājāgārake ambalaṭṭhikāyā”ti.**“At the royal rest-house at Ambalaṭṭhikā, between Rājagaha and Nāḷanda.”*";
P_HTM[13958]="*“Kaṃ ārabbhā”ti?**“Who is it about?”*";
P_HTM[13959]="*“Suppiyañca paribbājakaṃ brahmadattañca māṇavan”ti.**“The wanderer Suppiya and the young brahmin Brahmadatta.”*";
P_HTM[13960]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ brahmajālassa nidānampi pucchi, puggalampi pucchi.**And Mahākassapa asked Ānanda about the origin story of the Prime Net and about the person.*";
P_HTM[13961]="*“Sāmaññaphalaṃ panāvuso ānanda, kattha bhāsitan”ti?**“Where was the Fruits of the Monastic Life spoken?”*";
P_HTM[13962]="*“Rājagahe, bhante, jīvakambavane”ti.**“In Jīvaka’s mango grove at Rājagaha.”*";
P_HTM[13963]="*“Kena saddhin”ti?**“Who is it with?”*";
P_HTM[13964]="*“Ajātasattunā vedehiputtena saddhin”ti.**“Ajātasattu of Videha.”*";
P_HTM[13965]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ sāmaññaphalassa nidānampi pucchi, puggalampi pucchi.**And Mahākassapa asked Ānanda about the origin story of the Fruits of the Monastic Life and about the person.*";
P_HTM[13966]="*Eteneva upāyena pañcapi nikāye pucchi.**In this way he asked about the five collections.*";
P_HTM[13967]="*Puṭṭho puṭṭho āyasmā ānando vissajjesi.**And Ānanda was able to reply to every question.*";
P_HTM[13968]="*2. Khuddānukhuddakasikkhāpadakathā**2. Discussion of the lesser training rules*";
P_HTM[13969]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando there bhikkhū etadavoca—**Ānanda said to the senior monks,*";
P_HTM[13970]="*“bhagavā maṃ, bhante, parinibbānakāle evamāha—**“At the time of his final extinguishment, the Buddha said to me,*";
P_HTM[13971]="*‘ākaṅkhamāno, ānanda, saṅgho mamaccayena khuddānukhuddakāni sikkhāpadāni samūhaneyyā’”ti.**‘After my passing away, Ānanda, if the Sangha wishes, it may abolish the lesser training rules.’”*";
P_HTM[13972]="*“Pucchi pana tvaṃ, āvuso ānanda, bhagavantaṃ—**“But, Ānanda, did you ask the Buddha*";
P_HTM[13973]="*‘katamāni pana, bhante, khuddānukhuddakāni sikkhāpadānī’”ti?**which are the lesser training rules?”*";
P_HTM[13974]="*“Na khohaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ pucchiṃ—**“No, I didn’t.”*";
P_HTM[13975]="*‘katamāni pana, bhante, khuddānukhuddakāni sikkhāpadānī’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[13976]="*Ekacce therā evamāhaṃsu—**Some senior monks said,*";
P_HTM[13977]="*“cattāri pārājikāni ṭhapetvā, avasesāni khuddānukhuddakāni sikkhāpadānī”ti.**“Apart from the four rules entailing expulsion, the rest are the lesser training rules.”*";
P_HTM[13978]="*Ekacce therā evamāhaṃsu—**Others said,*";
P_HTM[13979]="*“cattāri pārājikāni ṭhapetvā, terasa saṅghādisese ṭhapetvā, avasesāni khuddānukhuddakāni sikkhāpadānī”ti.**“Apart from the four rules entailing expulsion and the thirteen rules entailing suspension, the rest are the lesser training rules.”*";
P_HTM[13980]="*Ekacce therā evamāhaṃsu—**Still others said,*";
P_HTM[13981]="*“cattāri pārājikāni ṭhapetvā, terasa saṅghādisese ṭhapetvā, dve aniyate ṭhapetvā, avasesāni khuddānukhuddakāni sikkhāpadānī”ti.**“Apart from the four rules entailing expulsion, the thirteen rules entailing suspension, and the two undetermined rules, the rest are the lesser training rules.”*";
P_HTM[13982]="*Ekacce therā evamāhaṃsu—**Still others said,*";
P_HTM[13983]="*“cattāri pārājikāni ṭhapetvā, terasa saṅghādisese ṭhapetvā, dve aniyate ṭhapetvā, tiṃsa nissaggiye pācittiye ṭhapetvā, avasesāni khuddānukhuddakāni sikkhāpadānī”ti.**“Apart from the four rules entailing expulsion, the thirteen rules entailing suspension, the two undetermined rules, and the thirty rules entailing relinquishment and confession, the rest are the lesser training rules.”*";
P_HTM[13984]="*Ekacce therā evamāhaṃsu—**Still others said,*";
P_HTM[13985]="*“cattāri pārājikāni ṭhapetvā, terasa saṅghādisese ṭhapetvā, dve aniyate ṭhapetvā, tiṃsa nissaggiye pācittiye ṭhapetvā, dvenavuti pācittiye ṭhapetvā, avasesāni khuddānukhuddakāni sikkhāpadānī”ti.**“Apart from the four rules entailing expulsion, the thirteen rules entailing suspension, the two undetermined rules, the thirty rules entailing relinquishment and confession, and the ninety-two rules entailing confession, the rest are the lesser training rules.”*";
P_HTM[13986]="*Ekacce therā evamāhaṃsu—**Still others said,*";
P_HTM[13987]="*“cattāri pārājikāni ṭhapetvā, terasa saṅghādisese ṭhapetvā, dve aniyate ṭhapetvā, tiṃsa nissaggiye pācittiye ṭhapetvā, dvenavuti pācittiye ṭhapetvā, cattāro pāṭidesanīye ṭhapetvā, avasesāni khuddānukhuddakāni sikkhāpadānī”ti.**“Apart from the four rules entailing expulsion, the thirteen rules entailing suspension, the two undetermined rules, the thirty rules entailing relinquishment and confession, the ninety-two rules entailing confession, and the four rules entailing acknowledgment, the rest are the lesser training rules.”*";
P_HTM[13988]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo saṅghaṃ ñāpesi—**Then Venerable Mahākassapa informed the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[13989]="*“Suṇātu me, āvuso, saṅgho.**“Please, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13990]="*Santamhākaṃ sikkhāpadāni gihigatāni.**We have training rules that relate to householders.*";
P_HTM[13991]="*Gihinopi jānanti—**The householders know*";
P_HTM[13992]="*‘idaṃ vo samaṇānaṃ sakyaputtiyānaṃ kappati, idaṃ vo na kappatī’ti.**what is allowable for us and what is not.*";
P_HTM[13993]="*Sace mayaṃ khuddānukhuddakāni sikkhāpadāni samūhanissāma, bhavissanti vattāro—**If we abolish the lesser training rules, some people will say,*";
P_HTM[13994]="*‘dhūmakālikaṃ samaṇena gotamena sāvakānaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ.**‘The ascetic Gotama laid down training rules for his disciples until the time of his death.*";
P_HTM[13995]="*Yāvimesaṃ satthā aṭṭhāsi tāvime sikkhāpadesu sikkhiṃsu.**But they practice the training rules only as long as their teacher is alive.*";
P_HTM[13996]="*Yato imesaṃ satthā parinibbuto, na dānime sikkhāpadesu sikkhantī’ti.**Since their teacher has now attained final extinguishment, they no longer practice the training rules.’*";
P_HTM[13997]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho apaññattaṃ nappaññapeyya, paññattaṃ na samucchindeyya, yathāpaññattesu sikkhāpadesu samādāya vatteyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should not lay down new rules, nor get rid of the existing ones, and it should undertake to practice the training rules as they are.*";
P_HTM[13998]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[13999]="*Suṇātu me, āvuso, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[14000]="*Santamhākaṃ sikkhāpadāni gihigatāni.**We have training rules that relate to householders.*";
P_HTM[14001]="*Gihinopi jānanti—**The householders know*";
P_HTM[14002]="*‘idaṃ vo samaṇānaṃ sakyaputtiyānaṃ kappati, idaṃ vo na kappatī’ti.**what is allowable for us and what is not.*";
P_HTM[14003]="*Sace mayaṃ khuddānukhuddakāni sikkhāpadāni samūhanissāma, bhavissanti vattāro—**If we abolish the lesser training rules, some people will say,*";
P_HTM[14004]="*‘dhūmakālikaṃ samaṇena gotamena sāvakānaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ.**‘The ascetic Gotama laid down training rules for his disciples until the time of his death.*";
P_HTM[14005]="*Yāvimesaṃ satthā aṭṭhāsi tāvime sikkhāpadesu sikkhiṃsu.**But they practice the training rules only as long as their teacher is alive.*";
P_HTM[14006]="*Yato imesaṃ satthā parinibbuto, na dānime sikkhāpadesu sikkhantī’ti.**Since their teacher has now attained final extinguishment, they no longer practice the training rules.’*";
P_HTM[14007]="*Saṅgho apaññattaṃ nappaññapeti, paññattaṃ na samucchindati, yathāpaññattesu sikkhāpadesu samādāya vattati.**The Sangha doesn’t lay down new rules, nor gets rid of the existing ones, and it undertakes to practice the training rules as they are.*";
P_HTM[14008]="*Yassāyasmato khamati apaññattassa appaññāpanā, paññattassa asamucchedo, yathāpaññattesu sikkhāpadesu samādāya vattanā, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of not laying down new rules, nor abolishing the old ones, and of undertaking to practice them as they are should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[14009]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[14010]="*Saṅgho apaññattaṃ nappaññapeti, paññattaṃ na samucchindati, yathāpaññattesu sikkhāpadesu samādāya vattati.**The Sangha doesn’t lay down new rules, nor gets rid of the existing ones, and it undertakes to practice the training rules as they are.*";
P_HTM[14011]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.”*";
P_HTM[14012]="*Atha kho therā bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavocuṃ—**The senior monks said,*";
P_HTM[14013]="*“idaṃ te, āvuso ānanda, dukkaṭaṃ, yaṃ tvaṃ bhagavantaṃ na pucchi—‘katamāni pana, bhante, khuddānukhuddakāni sikkhāpadānī’ti.**“You have committed an act of wrong conduct, Ānanda, in that you didn’t ask the Buddha which are the lesser training rules.*";
P_HTM[14014]="*Desehi taṃ dukkaṭan”ti.**Confess that wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[14015]="*“Ahaṃ kho, bhante, assatiyā bhagavantaṃ na pucchiṃ—‘katamāni pana, bhante, khuddānukhuddakāni sikkhāpadānī’ti.**“It was because of lack of mindfulness that I didn’t ask which are the lesser training rules.*";
P_HTM[14016]="*Nāhaṃ taṃ dukkaṭaṃ passāmi, api cāyasmantānaṃ saddhāya desemi taṃ dukkaṭan”ti.**I can’t see that I have committed any wrong conduct, but I’ll confess it out of faith in the venerables.”*";
P_HTM[14017]="*“Idampi te, āvuso ānanda, dukkaṭaṃ, yaṃ tvaṃ bhagavato vassikasāṭikaṃ akkamitvā sibbesi.**“You have also committed an act of wrong conduct in that you stepped on the Buddha’s rainy-season robe when you were sewing it.*";
P_HTM[14018]="*Desehi taṃ dukkaṭan”ti.**Confess that wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[14019]="*“Ahaṃ kho, bhante, na agāravena bhagavato vassikasāṭikaṃ akkamitvā sibbesiṃ.**“I didn’t step on it because of disrespect.*";
P_HTM[14020]="*Nāhaṃ taṃ dukkaṭaṃ passāmi, api cāyasmantānaṃ saddhāya desemi taṃ dukkaṭan”ti.**I can’t see that I’ve committed any wrong conduct, but I’ll confess it out of faith in the venerables.”*";
P_HTM[14021]="*“Idampi te, āvuso ānanda, dukkaṭaṃ, yaṃ tvaṃ mātugāmehi bhagavato sarīraṃ paṭhamaṃ vandāpesi, tāsaṃ rodantīnaṃ bhagavato sarīraṃ assukena makkhitaṃ.**“You have also committed an act of wrong conduct in that you had women pay respect to the Buddha’s dead body first. They soiled the Buddha’s body with tears.*";
P_HTM[14022]="*Desehi taṃ dukkaṭan”ti.**Confess that wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[14023]="*“Ahaṃ kho, bhante—māyimāsaṃ vikāle ahesunti—mātugāmehi bhagavato sarīraṃ paṭhamaṃ vandāpesiṃ.**“I did this so that it wouldn’t get too late for them.*";
P_HTM[14024]="*Nāhaṃ taṃ dukkaṭaṃ passāmi, api cāyasmantānaṃ saddhāya desemi taṃ dukkaṭan”ti.**I can’t see that I’ve committed any wrong conduct, but I’ll confess it out of faith in the venerables.”*";
P_HTM[14025]="*“Idampi te, āvuso ānanda, dukkaṭaṃ, yaṃ tvaṃ bhagavatā oḷārike nimitte kayiramāne, oḷārike obhāse kayiramāne, na bhagavantaṃ yāci—**“You have also committed an act of wrong conduct in that you didn’t, even when he gave you a broad hint, ask the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[14026]="*‘tiṭṭhatu bhagavā kappaṃ, tiṭṭhatu sugato kappaṃ, bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānan’ti.**‘Please live on for an eon—for the benefit and happiness of the humanity, out of compassion for the world, for the good, the benefit, and the happiness of gods and humans.’*";
P_HTM[14027]="*Desehi taṃ dukkaṭan”ti.**Confess that wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[14028]="*“Ahaṃ kho, bhante, mārena pariyuṭṭhitacitto na bhagavantaṃ yāciṃ—**“I didn’t ask because my mind was possessed by the Lord of Death.*";
P_HTM[14029]="*‘tiṭṭhatu bhagavā kappaṃ, tiṭṭhatu sugato kappaṃ, bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[14030]="*Nāhaṃ taṃ dukkaṭaṃ passāmi, api cāyasmantānaṃ saddhāya desemi taṃ dukkaṭan”ti.**I can’t see that I’ve committed any wrong conduct, but I’ll confess it out of faith in the venerables.”*";
P_HTM[14031]="*“Idampi te, āvuso ānanda, dukkaṭaṃ yaṃ tvaṃ mātugāmassa tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye pabbajjaṃ ussukkaṃ akāsi.**“You have also committed an act of wrong conduct in that you made an effort for women to be given the going forth on the spiritual path proclaimed by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[14032]="*Desehi taṃ dukkaṭan”ti.**Confess that wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[14033]="*“Ahaṃ kho, bhante, ayaṃ mahāpajāpati gotamī bhagavato mātucchā āpādikā posikā khīrassa dāyikā bhagavantaṃ janettiyā kālaṅkatāya thaññaṃ pāyesīti mātugāmassa tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye pabbajjaṃ ussukkaṃ akāsiṃ.**“I made this effort because Mahāpajāpati Gotamī was the Buddha’s aunt who nurtured him, brought him up, and breastfed him when his own mother died.*";
P_HTM[14034]="*Nāhaṃ taṃ dukkaṭaṃ passāmi, api cāyasmantānaṃ saddhāya desemi taṃ dukkaṭan”ti.**I can’t see that I’ve committed any wrong conduct, but I’ll confess it out of faith in the venerables.”*";
P_HTM[14035]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā purāṇo dakkhiṇāgirismiṃ cārikaṃ carati mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi.**At that time Venerable Purāṇa was wandering in the Southern Hills with a large sangha of five hundred monks.*";
P_HTM[14036]="*Atha kho āyasmā purāṇo therehi bhikkhūhi dhamme ca vinaye ca saṅgīte dakkhiṇāgirismiṃ yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena rājagahaṃ yena veḷuvanaṃ kalandakanivāpo yena therā bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā therehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ paṭisammoditvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**When the senior monks had concluded the communal recitation of the Teaching and the Monastic Law, and when Purāṇa had stayed in the Southern Hills for as long as he liked, he went to the Bamboo Grove at Rājagaha. There he went up to the senior monks, exchanged pleasantries with them, and sat down.*";
P_HTM[14037]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ purāṇaṃ therā bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—**And they said to him,*";
P_HTM[14038]="*“therehi, āvuso purāṇa, dhammo ca vinayo ca saṅgīto.**“Purāṇa, the senior monks have jointly recited the Teaching and the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[14039]="*Upehi taṃ saṅgītin”ti.**Please accept that communal recitation.”*";
P_HTM[14040]="*“Susaṅgītāvuso, therehi dhammo ca vinayo ca.**“The Teaching and the Monastic Law have been well-recited by the senior monks.*";
P_HTM[14041]="*Api ca yatheva mayā bhagavato sammukhā sutaṃ, sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ, tathevāhaṃ dhāressāmī”ti.**Nevertheless, I’ll remember what I myself have received in the presence of the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[14042]="*3. Brahmadaṇḍakathā**3. Discussion of the supreme penalty*";
P_HTM[14043]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando there bhikkhū etadavoca—**And Venerable Ānanda said to the senior monks,*";
P_HTM[14044]="*“bhagavā maṃ, bhante, parinibbānakāle evamāha—**“At the time of his final extinguishment, the Buddha said to me,*";
P_HTM[14045]="*‘tena hānanda, saṅgho mamaccayena channassa bhikkhuno brahmadaṇḍaṃ āṇāpetū’”ti.**‘After my passing away, Ānanda, the Sangha should impose the supreme penalty on the monk Channa.’”*";
P_HTM[14046]="*“Pucchi pana tvaṃ, āvuso ānanda, bhagavantaṃ—**“Did you ask the Buddha*";
P_HTM[14047]="*‘katamo pana, bhante, brahmadaṇḍo’”ti?**what the supreme penalty is?”*";
P_HTM[14048]="*“Pucchiṃ khohaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ—**“I did,*";
P_HTM[14049]="*‘katamo pana, bhante, brahmadaṇḍo’ti?* **";
P_HTM[14050]="*‘Channo, ānanda, bhikkhu yaṃ iccheyya taṃ vadeyya.**and he replied, ‘Whatever Channa says,*";
P_HTM[14051]="*Bhikkhūhi channo bhikkhu neva vattabbo, na ovaditabbo, nānusāsitabbo’”ti.**the monks should not correct him, instruct him, or teach him.’”*";
P_HTM[14052]="*“Tena hāvuso ānanda, tvaṃyeva channassa bhikkhuno brahmadaṇḍaṃ āṇāpehī”ti.**“Well then, Ānanda, impose the supreme penalty on Channa.”*";
P_HTM[14053]="*“Kathāhaṃ, bhante, channassa bhikkhuno brahmadaṇḍaṃ āṇāpemi, caṇḍo so bhikkhu pharuso”ti?**“But how should I do it? Channa is violent and harsh.”*";
P_HTM[14054]="*“Tena hāvuso ānanda, bahukehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ gacchāhī”ti.**“Go together with many monks.”*";
P_HTM[14055]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ paṭissutvā mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi nāvāya ujjavanikāya kosambiṃ ujjavi, nāvāya paccorohitvā rañño udenassa uyyānassa avidūre aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle nisīdi.**Saying, “Yes, Venerables,” he traveled by boat upstream to Kosambī with a large sangha of five hundred monks. After disembarking, he sat down at the foot of a tree not far from King Udena’s park.*";
P_HTM[14056]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājā udeno uyyāne paricāresi saddhiṃ orodhena.**Just then King Udena was enjoying himself in the park together with his harem.*";
P_HTM[14057]="*Assosi kho rañño udenassa orodho—**The harem women had heard*";
P_HTM[14058]="*“amhākaṃ kira ācariyo ayyo ānando uyyānassa avidūre aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle nisinno”ti.**that their teacher, Venerable Ānanda, was seated at the foot of a tree not far from the park.*";
P_HTM[14059]="*Atha kho rañño udenassa orodho rājānaṃ udenaṃ etadavoca—**They told the King,*";
P_HTM[14060]="*“amhākaṃ kira, deva, ācariyo ayyo ānando uyyānassa avidūre aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle nisinno.* **";
P_HTM[14061]="*Icchāma mayaṃ, deva, ayyaṃ ānandaṃ passitun”ti.**adding, “Sir, we would like to see Venerable Ānanda.”*";
P_HTM[14062]="*“Tena hi tumhe samaṇaṃ ānandaṃ passathā”ti.**“Well then, go ahead.”*";
P_HTM[14063]="*Atha kho rañño udenassa orodho yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**The harem women then went to Ānanda, bowed, and sat down.*";
P_HTM[14064]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho rañño udenassa orodhaṃ āyasmā ānando dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi.**And Ānanda instructed, inspired, and gladdened them with a teaching,*";
P_HTM[14065]="*Atha kho rañño udenassa orodho āyasmatā ānandena dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito āyasmato ānandassa pañca uttarāsaṅgasatāni pādāsi.**at the end of which they gave him five hundred upper robes.*";
P_HTM[14066]="*Atha kho rañño udenassa orodho āyasmato ānandassa bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā yena rājā udeno tenupasaṅkami.**After rejoicing and expressing their appreciation for his teaching, they got up from their seats, bowed down, circumambulated him with their right side toward him, and went to King Udena.*";
P_HTM[14067]="*Addasā kho rājā udeno orodhaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**When King Udena saw them coming,*";
P_HTM[14068]="*Disvāna orodhaṃ etadavoca—**he said to them,*";
P_HTM[14069]="*“api nu kho tumhe samaṇaṃ ānandaṃ passitthā”ti?**“Did you see the ascetic Ānanda?”*";
P_HTM[14070]="*“Apassimhā kho mayaṃ, deva, ayyaṃ ānandan”ti.**“We did.”*";
P_HTM[14071]="*“Api nu tumhe samaṇassa ānandassa kiñci adatthā”ti?**“Did you give him anything?”*";
P_HTM[14072]="*“Adamhā kho mayaṃ, deva, ayyassa ānandassa pañca uttarāsaṅgasatānī”ti.**“We gave him five hundred upper robes.”*";
P_HTM[14073]="*Rājā udeno ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**King Udena complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[14074]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇo ānando tāva bahuṃ cīvaraṃ paṭiggahessati.**“How can the ascetic Ānanda receive so many robes?*";
P_HTM[14075]="*Dussavāṇijjaṃ vā samaṇo ānando karissati, paggāhikasālaṃ vā pasāressatī”ti.**Is he starting up as cloth merchant or setting up shop?”*";
P_HTM[14076]="*Atha kho rājā udeno yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ sammodi.**King Udena then went to Ānanda, exchanged pleasantries with him,*";
P_HTM[14077]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**sat down,*";
P_HTM[14078]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho rājā udeno āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[14079]="*“āgamā nu khvidha, bho ānanda, amhākaṃ orodho”ti?**“Sir Ānanda, did our harem women come here?”*";
P_HTM[14080]="*“Āgamāsi kho te idha, mahārāja, orodho”ti.**“They did.”*";
P_HTM[14081]="*“Api pana bhoto ānandassa kiñci adāsī”ti?**“Did they give you anything?”*";
P_HTM[14082]="*“Adāsi kho me, mahārāja, pañca uttarāsaṅgasatānī”ti.**“They gave me five hundred upper robes.”*";
P_HTM[14083]="*“Kiṃ pana bhavaṃ ānando tāva bahuṃ cīvaraṃ karissatī”ti?**“But what will you do with five hundred robes?”*";
P_HTM[14084]="*“Ye te, mahārāja, bhikkhū dubbalacīvarā tehi saddhiṃ saṃvibhajissāmī”ti.**“I’ll share them with those monks whose robes are worn.”*";
P_HTM[14085]="*“Yāni kho pana, bho ānanda, porāṇakāni dubbalacīvarāni tāni kathaṃ karissathā”ti?**“And what will you do with the worn robes?”*";
P_HTM[14086]="*“Tāni, mahārāja, uttarattharaṇaṃ karissāmā”ti.**“We’ll make them into bedspreads.”*";
P_HTM[14087]="*“Yāni pana, bho ānanda, porāṇakāni uttarattharaṇāni tāni kathaṃ karissathā”ti?**“And what will you do with the old bedspreads?”*";
P_HTM[14088]="*“Tāni, mahārāja, bhisicchaviyo karissāmā”ti.**“We’ll make them into mattress covers.”*";
P_HTM[14089]="*“Yā pana, bho ānanda, porāṇakā bhisicchaviyo tā kathaṃ karissathā”ti?**“And what will you do with the old mattress covers?”*";
P_HTM[14090]="*“Tā, mahārāja, bhūmattharaṇaṃ karissāmā”ti.**“We’ll make them into floor covers.”*";
P_HTM[14091]="*“Yāni pana, bho ānanda, porāṇakāni bhūmattharaṇāni tāni kathaṃ karissathā”ti?**“And what will you do with the old floor covers?”*";
P_HTM[14092]="*“Tāni, mahārāja, pādapuñchaniyo karissāmā”ti.**“We’ll make them into doormats.”*";
P_HTM[14093]="*“Yā pana, bho ānanda, porāṇakā pādapuñchaniyo tā kathaṃ karissathā”ti?**“And what will you do with the old doormats?”*";
P_HTM[14094]="*“Tā, mahārāja, rajoharaṇaṃ karissāmā”ti.**“We’ll make them into dustcloths.”*";
P_HTM[14095]="*“Yāni pana, bho ānanda, porāṇakāni rajoharaṇāni tāni kathaṃ karissathā”ti?**“And what will you do with the old dustcloths?”*";
P_HTM[14096]="*“Tāni, mahārāja, koṭṭetvā cikkhallena madditvā paribhaṇḍaṃ limpissāmā”ti.**“We’ll cut them up, mix them with mud, and smear the floors.”*";
P_HTM[14097]="*Atha kho rājā udeno—“sabbevime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā yoniso upanenti, na kulavaṃ gamentī”ti—**King Udena thought, “These Sakyan monastics are clever at putting things to use; nothing is wasted,”*";
P_HTM[14098]="*āyasmato ānandassa aññānipi pañca dussasatāni pādāsi.**and he gave another five hundred pieces of cloth to Ānanda.*";
P_HTM[14099]="*Ayañcarahi āyasmato ānandassa paṭhamaṃ cīvarabhikkhā uppajji cīvarasahassaṃ.**Together with the first offering of robes, Ānanda was given a total of a thousand robes.*";
P_HTM[14100]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena ghositārāmo tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**Ānanda then went to Ghosita’s Monastery, where he sat down on the prepared seat.*";
P_HTM[14101]="*Atha kho āyasmā channo yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Venerable Channa went up to Ānanda, bowed, and sat down.*";
P_HTM[14102]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ channaṃ āyasmā ānando etadavoca—**And Ānanda said,*";
P_HTM[14103]="*“saṅghena te, āvuso channa, brahmadaṇḍo āṇāpito”ti.**“Channa, the Sangha has imposed the supreme penalty on you.”*";
P_HTM[14104]="*“Katamo pana, bhante ānanda, brahmadaṇḍo āṇāpito”ti?**“What’s the supreme penalty?”*";
P_HTM[14105]="*“Tvaṃ, āvuso channa, bhikkhū yaṃ iccheyyāsi taṃ vadeyyāsi.**“Whatever you say to the monks,*";
P_HTM[14106]="*Bhikkhūhi tvaṃ neva vattabbo, na ovaditabbo, nānusāsitabbo”ti.**the monks should not correct you, instruct you, or teach you.”*";
P_HTM[14107]="*“Nanvāhaṃ, bhante ānanda, hato ettāvatā, yatohaṃ bhikkhūhi neva vattabbo, na ovaditabbo, nānusāsitabbo”ti tattheva mucchito papato.**Saying, “I’m ruined!” he fainted on the spot.*";
P_HTM[14108]="*Atha kho āyasmā channo brahmadaṇḍena aṭṭīyamāno harāyamāno jigucchamāno eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto nacirasseva—**Being troubled, ashamed, and disgusted by the supreme penalty, Channa stayed by himself, secluded, heedful, energetic, and diligent.*";
P_HTM[14109]="*yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—**And in this very life, he soon realized with his own insight the supreme goal of the spiritual life for which people from good families rightly go forth into homelessness.*";
P_HTM[14110]="*brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi.* **";
P_HTM[14111]="*“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti abbhaññāsi.**He understood that birth had come to an end, that the spiritual life had been fulfilled, that the job had been done, that there was no further state of existence.*";
P_HTM[14112]="*Aññataro ca panāyasmā channo arahataṃ ahosi.**And Venerable Channa became one of the perfected ones.*";
P_HTM[14113]="*Atha kho āyasmā channo arahattaṃ patto yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca—**He then went to Ānanda and said,*";
P_HTM[14114]="*“paṭippassambhehi dāni me, bhante ānanda, brahmadaṇḍan”ti.**“Venerable Ānanda, please lift the supreme penalty.”*";
P_HTM[14115]="*“Yadaggena tayā, āvuso channa, arahattaṃ sacchikataṃ tadaggena te brahmadaṇḍo paṭippassaddho”ti.**“The moment you realized perfection, the supreme penalty was lifted.”*";
P_HTM[14116]="*Imāya kho pana vinayasaṅgītiyā pañca bhikkhusatāni anūnāni anadhikāni ahesuṃ.**At this communal recitation of the Monastic Law there were five hundred monks, neither more nor less.*";
P_HTM[14117]="*Tasmā ayaṃ vinayasaṅgīti “pañcasatikā”ti vuccatīti.**For this reason this communal recitation is called “The group of five hundred”.*";
P_HTM[14118]="*Pañcasatikakkhandhako ekādasamo. Imamhi khandhake vatthū tevīsati.**The eleventh chapter on the group of five hundred is finished. In this chapter there are twenty-three topics.*";
P_HTM[14119]="*Tassuddānaṃ* **";
P_HTM[14120]="*Parinibbute sambuddhe,* **";
P_HTM[14121]="*thero kassapasavhayo;* **";
P_HTM[14122]="*Āmantayi bhikkhugaṇaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[14123]="*saddhammamanupālako.* **";
P_HTM[14124]="*Pāvāyaddhānamaggamhi,* **";
P_HTM[14125]="*subhaddena paveditaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[14126]="*Saṅgāyissāma saddhammaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[14127]="*adhammo pure dippati.* **";
P_HTM[14128]="*Ekenūna pañcasataṃ,* **";
P_HTM[14129]="*ānandampi ca uccini;* **";
P_HTM[14130]="*Dhammavinayasaṅgītiṃ,* **";
P_HTM[14131]="*vasanto guhamuttame.* **";
P_HTM[14132]="*Upāliṃ vinayaṃ pucchi,* **";
P_HTM[14133]="*suttantānandapaṇḍitaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[14134]="*Piṭakaṃ tīṇi saṅgītiṃ,* **";
P_HTM[14135]="*akaṃsu jinasāvakā.* **";
P_HTM[14136]="*Khuddānukhuddake nānā,* **";
P_HTM[14137]="*yathāpaññattivattanā;* **";
P_HTM[14138]="*Na pucchi akkamitvāna,* **";
P_HTM[14139]="*vandāpesi na yāci ca.* **";
P_HTM[14140]="*Pabbajjaṃ mātugāmassa,* **";
P_HTM[14141]="*saddhāya dukkaṭāni me;* **";
P_HTM[14142]="*Purāṇo brahmadaṇḍañca,* **";
P_HTM[14143]="*orodho udenena saha.* **";
P_HTM[14144]="*Tāva bahu dubbalañca,* **";
P_HTM[14145]="*uttarattharaṇā bhisi;* **";
P_HTM[14146]="*Bhūmattharaṇā puñchaniyo,* **";
P_HTM[14147]="*rajo cikkhallamaddanā.* **";
P_HTM[14148]="*Sahassacīvaraṃ uppajji,* **";
P_HTM[14149]="*paṭhamānandasavhayo;* **";
P_HTM[14150]="*Tajjito brahmadaṇḍena,* **";
P_HTM[14151]="*catussaccaṃ apāpuṇi;* **";
P_HTM[14152]="*Vasībhūtā pañcasatā,* **";
P_HTM[14153]="*tasmā pañcasatī iti.* **";
P_HTM[14154]="*Pañcasatikakkhandhako niṭṭhito.**The chapter on the group of five hundred is finished.*";
P_HTM[14155]="*12. Sattasatikakkhandhaka **12.  The chapter on the group of seven hundred *";
P_HTM[14156]="*Tena kho pana samayena vassasataparinibbute bhagavati vesālikā vajjiputtakā bhikkhū vesāliyaṃ dasa vatthūni dīpenti—**One hundred years after the Buddha had attained final extinguishment, the Vajjian monks of Vesālī proclaimed ten practices as allowable:*";
P_HTM[14157]="*kappati siṅgiloṇakappo, kappati dvaṅgulakappo, kappati gāmantarakappo, kappati āvāsakappo, kappati anumatikappo, kappati āciṇṇakappo, kappati amathitakappo, kappati jaḷogiṃ pātuṃ, kappati adasakaṃ nisīdanaṃ, kappati jātarūparajatanti.**the salt-in-horn practice; the two fingerbreadths practice; the next-village practice; the many-monasteries practice; the consent practice; customary practices; the unchurned practice; palm-juice drinking; sitting mats without borders; and gold, silver, and money.*";
P_HTM[14158]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā yaso kākaṇḍakaputto vajjīsu cārikaṃ caramāno yena vesālī tadavasari.**At that time Venerable Yasa of Kākaṇḍa was wandering in the Vajjian country, when he arrived at Vesālī.*";
P_HTM[14159]="*Tatra sudaṃ āyasmā yaso kākaṇḍakaputto vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ.**There he stayed in the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood.*";
P_HTM[14160]="*Tena kho pana samayena vesālikā vajjiputtakā bhikkhū tadahuposathe kaṃsapātiṃ udakena pūretvā majjhe bhikkhusaṅghassa ṭhapetvā āgatāgate vesālike upāsake evaṃ vadanti—**Soon afterwards, on the day of the observance procedure, the Vajjian monks of Vesālī filled a bronze bowl with water and placed it in the midst of the Sangha of monks. Whenever a lay follower of Vesālī came, they said,*";
P_HTM[14161]="*“dethāvuso, saṅghassa kahāpaṇampi aḍḍhampi pādampi māsakarūpampi.**“Give a _kahāpaṇa_ coin to the Sangha, or half a _kahāpaṇa_, or a _pāda_, or a _māsaka_.*";
P_HTM[14162]="*Bhavissati saṅghassa parikkhārena karaṇīyan”ti.**The Sangha needs requisites.”*";
P_HTM[14163]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā yaso kākaṇḍakaputto vesālike upāsake etadavoca—**But Yaso said to the lay followers,*";
P_HTM[14164]="*“māvuso, adattha saṅghassa kahāpaṇampi aḍḍhampi pādampi māsakarūpampi.**“Don’t give a _kahāpaṇa_ to the Sangha, or half a _kahāpaṇa_, or a _pāda_, or a _māsaka_.*";
P_HTM[14165]="*Na kappati samaṇānaṃ sakyaputtiyānaṃ jātarūparajataṃ;**Gold, silver, and money are not allowable for the Sakyan monastics.*";
P_HTM[14166]="*na sādiyanti samaṇā sakyaputtiyā jātarūparajataṃ;**They neither accept*";
P_HTM[14167]="*na paṭiggaṇhanti samaṇā sakyaputtiyā jātarūparajataṃ;**nor receive gold, silver, and money.*";
P_HTM[14168]="*nikkhittamaṇisuvaṇṇā samaṇā sakyaputtiyā apetajātarūparajatā”ti.**The Sakyan monastics have given up gems and gold, and live without gold, silver, and money.”*";
P_HTM[14169]="*Evampi kho vesālikā upāsakā āyasmatā yasena kākaṇḍakaputtena vuccamānā adaṃsuyeva saṅghassa kahāpaṇampi aḍḍhampi pādampi māsakarūpampi.**But although Yasa said this, the lay followers continued to give money to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[14170]="*Atha kho vesālikā vajjiputtakā bhikkhū tassā rattiyā accayena taṃ hiraññaṃ bhikkhaggena paṭivīsaṃ ṭhapetvā bhājesuṃ.**The next morning the Vajjian monks shared out the money evenly.*";
P_HTM[14171]="*Atha kho vesālikā vajjiputtakā bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ yasaṃ kākaṇḍakaputtaṃ etadavocuṃ—**And they said to Yasa,*";
P_HTM[14172]="*“eso te, āvuso yasa, hiraññassa paṭivīso”ti.**“Here is your share, Yasa.”*";
P_HTM[14173]="*“Natthi me, āvuso, hiraññassa paṭivīso, nāhaṃ hiraññaṃ sādiyāmī”ti.**“There is no share for me. I don’t accept money.”*";
P_HTM[14174]="*Atha kho vesālikā vajjiputtakā bhikkhū—**The Vajjian monks said to one another,*";
P_HTM[14175]="*“ayaṃ, āvuso, yaso kākaṇḍakaputto upāsake saddhe pasanne akkosati, paribhāsati, appasādaṃ karoti;**“Yasa is abusing and reviling the lay followers who have faith and confidence. He’s destroying their confidence.*";
P_HTM[14176]="*handassa mayaṃ paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ karomā”ti te tassa paṭisāraṇīyakammaṃ akaṃsu.**Let’s do a legal procedure of reconciliation against him.” And they did just that.*";
P_HTM[14177]="*Atha kho āyasmā yaso kākaṇḍakaputto vesālike vajjiputtake bhikkhū etadavoca—**Yasa said to them,*";
P_HTM[14178]="*“bhagavatā, āvuso, paññattaṃ—**“The Buddha has laid down*";
P_HTM[14179]="*‘paṭisāraṇīyakammakatassa bhikkhuno anudūto dātabbo’ti.**that a monk who has had a legal procedure of reconciliation done against himself should be given a monk as companion messenger.*";
P_HTM[14180]="*Detha me, āvuso, anudūtaṃ bhikkhun”ti.**Please give me a companion monk.”*";
P_HTM[14181]="*Atha kho vesālikā vajjiputtakā bhikkhū ekaṃ bhikkhuṃ sammannitvā āyasmato yasassa kākaṇḍakaputtassa anudūtaṃ adaṃsu.**They appointed one monk and gave him to Yasa as companion messenger.*";
P_HTM[14182]="*Atha kho āyasmā yaso kākaṇḍakaputto anudūtena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ vesāliṃ pavisitvā vesālike upāsake etadavoca—**Yasa entered Vesālī with his companion and said to the lay followers there,*";
P_HTM[14183]="*“ahaṃ kirāyasmante upāsake saddhe pasanne akkosāmi, paribhāsāmi, appasādaṃ karomi;**“It seems that I’m abusing and reviling the venerable lay followers who have faith and confidence, and that I’m destroying their confidence,*";
P_HTM[14184]="*yohaṃ adhammaṃ adhammoti vadāmi, dhammaṃ dhammoti vadāmi, avinayaṃ avinayoti vadāmi, vinayaṃ vinayoti vadāmi.**since I speak of what is contrary to the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching and of the Teaching as the Teaching, and since I speak of what is contrary to the Monastic Law as contrary to the Monastic Law and of the Monastic Law as the Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[14185]="*Ekamidaṃ, āvuso, samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**“On one occasion the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[14186]="*Tatra kho, āvuso, bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi—**There he addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[14187]="*‘cattārome, bhikkhave, candimasūriyānaṃ upakkilesā, yehi upakkilesehi upakkiliṭṭhā candimasūriyā na tapanti, na bhāsanti, na virocanti.**‘There are these four defilements of the sun and the moon that stop them from shining and radiating:*";
P_HTM[14188]="*Katame cattāro? Abbhaṃ, bhikkhave, candimasūriyānaṃ upakkileso, yena upakkilesena upakkiliṭṭhā candimasūriyā na tapanti, na bhāsanti na virocanti.**clouds;*";
P_HTM[14189]="*Mahikā, bhikkhave, candimasūriyānaṃ upakkileso, yena upakkilesena upakkiliṭṭhā candimasūriyā na tapanti, na bhāsanti, na virocanti.**snow;*";
P_HTM[14190]="*Dhūmarajo, bhikkhave, candimasūriyānaṃ upakkileso, yena upakkilesena upakkiliṭṭhā candimasūriyā na tapanti, na bhāsanti, na virocanti.**smoke and dust;*";
P_HTM[14191]="*Rāhu, bhikkhave, asurindo candimasūriyānaṃ upakkileso, yena upakkilesena upakkiliṭṭhā candimasūriyā na tapanti, na bhāsanti, na virocanti.**and an eclipse by Rāhu, the ruler of the antigods.*";
P_HTM[14192]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro candimasūriyānaṃ upakkilesā, yehi upakkilesehi upakkiliṭṭhā candimasūriyā na tapanti, na bhāsanti, na virocanti.* **";
P_HTM[14193]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, cattārome samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ upakkilesā, yehi upakkilesehi upakkiliṭṭhā eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā na tapanti, na bhāsanti, na virocanti.**In the same way, there are these four defilements of monastics and brahmins that stop them from shining and radiating:*";
P_HTM[14194]="*Katame cattāro?* **";
P_HTM[14195]="*Santi, bhikkhave, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā suraṃ pivanti, merayaṃ pivanti, surāmerayapānā appaṭiviratā—**drinking alcohol;*";
P_HTM[14196]="*ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ upakkileso, yena upakkilesena upakkiliṭṭhā eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā na tapanti, na bhāsanti, na virocanti.* **";
P_HTM[14197]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevanti, methunadhammā appaṭiviratā—**having sexual intercourse;*";
P_HTM[14198]="*ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ upakkileso, yena upakkilesena upakkiliṭṭhā eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā na tapanti, na bhāsanti, na virocanti.* **";
P_HTM[14199]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā jātarūparajataṃ sādiyanti, jātarūparajatappaṭiggahaṇā appaṭiviratā—**accepting gold, silver, and money;*";
P_HTM[14200]="*ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ upakkileso, yena upakkilesena upakkiliṭṭhā eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā na tapanti, na bhāsanti, na virocanti.* **";
P_HTM[14201]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā micchājīvena jīvitaṃ kappenti;**and making a living through wrong livelihood.’*";
P_HTM[14202]="*micchājīvā appaṭiviratā—* **";
P_HTM[14203]="*ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ upakkileso, yena upakkilesena upakkiliṭṭhā eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā na tapanti, na bhāsanti, na virocanti.* **";
P_HTM[14204]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ upakkilesā, yehi upakkilesehi upakkiliṭṭhā eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā na tapanti, na bhāsanti, na virocanti’.* **";
P_HTM[14205]="*Idamavocāvuso, bhagavā.* **";
P_HTM[14206]="*Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā—**Having said this, the Teacher added:*";
P_HTM[14207]="*‘Rāgadosaparikliṭṭhā,**‘Defiled by desire and ill will,*";
P_HTM[14208]="*eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā;**Some monastics and brahmins,*";
P_HTM[14209]="*Avijjānivuṭā posā,**Those hindered by delusion,*";
P_HTM[14210]="*piyarūpābhinandino.**Delight in what seems lovely.*";
P_HTM[14211]="*Suraṃ pivanti merayaṃ,**Some monastics and brahmins—*";
P_HTM[14212]="*paṭisevanti methunaṃ;**Deluded, they drink alcohol,*";
P_HTM[14213]="*Rajataṃ jātarūpañca,**Have sexual intercourse,*";
P_HTM[14214]="*sādiyanti aviddasū.**Accept gold, silver, and money,*";
P_HTM[14215]="*Micchājīvena jīvanti,**And make a living*";
P_HTM[14216]="*eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā;**Through wrong livelihood.*";
P_HTM[14217]="*Ete upakkilesā vuttā,**These are called defilements by the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[14218]="*buddhenādiccabandhunā.**The Kinsman of the Sun.*";
P_HTM[14219]="*Yehi upakkilesehi upakkiliṭṭhā,**Those monastics and brahmins*";
P_HTM[14220]="*Eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā;**Who are defiled by these*";
P_HTM[14221]="*Na tapanti na bhāsanti,**Do not shine and radiate;*";
P_HTM[14222]="*Asuddhā sarajā magā.**They are impure, dirty, and low.*";
P_HTM[14223]="*Andhakārena onaddhā,**Enveloped in darkness,*";
P_HTM[14224]="*taṇhādāsā sanettikā;**Slaves to craving that leads them on,*";
P_HTM[14225]="*Vaḍḍhenti kaṭasiṃ ghoraṃ,**Filling the dreaded cemeteries,*";
P_HTM[14226]="*ādiyanti punabbhavan’ti.**They receive another life.’*";
P_HTM[14227]="*Evaṃvādī kirāhaṃ āyasmante upāsake saddhe pasanne akkosāmi, paribhāsāmi, appasādaṃ karomi;**It’s by speaking like this, it seems, that I’m abusing and reviling the venerable lay followers who have faith and confidence, and that I’m destroying their confidence.*";
P_HTM[14228]="*yohaṃ adhammaṃ adhammoti vadāmi, dhammaṃ dhammoti vadāmi, avinayaṃ avinayoti vadāmi, vinayaṃ vinayoti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[14229]="*Ekamidaṃ, āvuso, samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**“At one time when the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove,*";
P_HTM[14230]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājantepure rājaparisāyaṃ sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ ayamantarakathā udapādi—**the royal court was seated together in the royal compound, having the following conversation,*";
P_HTM[14231]="*‘kappati samaṇānaṃ sakyaputtiyānaṃ jātarūparajataṃ;**‘Gold, silver, and money are allowable for the Sakyan monastics;*";
P_HTM[14232]="*sādiyanti samaṇā sakyaputtiyā jātarūparajataṃ;**they accept*";
P_HTM[14233]="*paṭiggaṇhanti samaṇā sakyaputtiyā jātarūparajatan’ti.**and receive gold, silver, and money.’*";
P_HTM[14234]="*Tena kho panāvuso, samayena maṇicūḷako gāmaṇī tassaṃ parisāyaṃ nisinno hoti.**On that occasion the chief Maṇicūlaka was sitting in that gathering.*";
P_HTM[14235]="*Atha kho, āvuso, maṇicūḷako gāmaṇī taṃ parisaṃ etadavoca—**He said,*";
P_HTM[14236]="*‘mā, ayyā, evaṃ avacuttha.**‘No,*";
P_HTM[14237]="*Na kappati samaṇānaṃ sakyaputtiyānaṃ jātarūparajataṃ;**gold, silver, and money are not allowable for the Sakyan monastics.*";
P_HTM[14238]="*na sādiyanti samaṇā sakyaputtiyā jātarūparajataṃ;**They neither accept*";
P_HTM[14239]="*na paṭiggaṇhanti samaṇā sakyaputtiyā jātarūparajataṃ;**nor receive gold, silver, or money.*";
P_HTM[14240]="*nikkhittamaṇisuvaṇṇā samaṇā sakyaputtiyā apetajātarūparajatā’ti.**The Sakyan monastics have given up gems and gold, and live without gold, silver, and money.’*";
P_HTM[14241]="*Asakkhi kho, āvuso, maṇicūḷako gāmaṇī taṃ parisaṃ saññāpetuṃ.**And he was able to persuade the gathering.*";
P_HTM[14242]="*Atha kho, āvuso, maṇicūḷako gāmaṇī taṃ parisaṃ saññāpetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Soon afterwards Maṇicūlaka went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[14243]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho, āvuso, maṇicūḷako gāmaṇī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and told him what had happened,*";
P_HTM[14244]="*‘idha, bhante, rājantepure rājaparisāyaṃ sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ ayamantarakathā udapādi—* **";
P_HTM[14245]="*kappati samaṇānaṃ sakyaputtiyānaṃ jātarūparajataṃ;* **";
P_HTM[14246]="*sādiyanti samaṇā sakyaputtiyā jātarūparajataṃ;* **";
P_HTM[14247]="*paṭiggaṇhanti samaṇā sakyaputtiyā jātarūparajatanti.* **";
P_HTM[14248]="*Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhante, taṃ parisaṃ etadavocaṃ—* **";
P_HTM[14249]="*mā, ayyā, evaṃ avacuttha.* **";
P_HTM[14250]="*Na kappati samaṇānaṃ sakyaputtiyānaṃ jātarūparajataṃ;* **";
P_HTM[14251]="*na sādiyanti samaṇā sakyaputtiyā jātarūparajataṃ;* **";
P_HTM[14252]="*na paṭiggaṇhanti samaṇā sakyaputtiyā jātarūparajataṃ;* **";
P_HTM[14253]="*nikkhittamaṇisuvaṇṇā samaṇā sakyaputtiyā apetajātarūparajatāti.* **";
P_HTM[14254]="*Asakkhiṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, taṃ parisaṃ saññāpetuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[14255]="*Kaccāhaṃ, bhante, evaṃ byākaramāno vuttavādī ceva bhagavato homi, na ca bhagavantaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkhāmi, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākaromi, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgacchatī’ti?**adding, ‘Venerable Sir, have I explained in accordance with the Teaching so that I can’t be legitimately criticized or censured?’*";
P_HTM[14256]="*‘Taggha tvaṃ, gāmaṇi, evaṃ byākaramāno vuttavādī ceva me hosi;**‘You certainly have.*";
P_HTM[14257]="*na ca maṃ abhūtena abbhācikkhasi, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākarosi, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgacchati.* **";
P_HTM[14258]="*Na hi, gāmaṇi, kappati samaṇānaṃ sakyaputtiyānaṃ jātarūparajataṃ;**For gold, silver, and money are not allowable for the Sakyan monastics.*";
P_HTM[14259]="*na sādiyanti samaṇā sakyaputtiyā jātarūparajataṃ;**They neither accept*";
P_HTM[14260]="*na paṭiggaṇhanti samaṇā sakyaputtiyā jātarūparajataṃ;**nor receive gold, silver, or money.*";
P_HTM[14261]="*nikkhittamaṇisuvaṇṇā samaṇā sakyaputtiyā apetajātarūparajatā.**The Sakyan monastics have given up gems and gold, and live without gold, silver, and money.*";
P_HTM[14262]="*Yassa kho, gāmaṇi, jātarūparajataṃ kappati, pañcapi tassa kāmaguṇā kappanti.**Whoever is allowed gold, silver, and money is also allowed the pleasures of the world.*";
P_HTM[14263]="*Yassa pañca kāmaguṇā kappanti ekaṃsenetaṃ, gāmaṇi, dhāreyyāsi—**And you should know that anyone who is allowed the pleasures of the world*";
P_HTM[14264]="*assamaṇadhammo asakyaputtiyadhammoti.**does not have the qualities of an ascetic, the qualities of a Sakyan monastic.*";
P_HTM[14265]="*Api cāhaṃ, gāmaṇi, evaṃ vadāmi tiṇaṃ tiṇatthikena pariyesitabbaṃ;**Still, I say that anyone who needs grass may look for it,*";
P_HTM[14266]="*dāru dārutthikena pariyesitabbaṃ;**likewise timber,*";
P_HTM[14267]="*sakaṭaṃ sakaṭatthikena pariyesitabbaṃ;**a cart,*";
P_HTM[14268]="*puriso purisatthikena pariyesitabbo.**or a worker.*";
P_HTM[14269]="*Na tvevāhaṃ, gāmaṇi, kenaci pariyāyena jātarūparajataṃ sāditabbaṃ pariyesitabbanti vadāmī’ti.**But under no circumstances should they accept or look for gold, silver, or money.’*";
P_HTM[14270]="*Evaṃvādī kirāhaṃ āyasmante upāsake saddhe pasanne akkosāmi, paribhāsāmi, appasādaṃ karomi;**It’s by speaking like this, it seems, that I’m abusing and reviling the venerable lay followers who have faith and confidence, and that I’m destroying their confidence.*";
P_HTM[14271]="*yohaṃ adhammaṃ adhammoti vadāmi, dhammaṃ dhammoti vadāmi, avinayaṃ avinayoti vadāmi, vinayaṃ vinayoti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[14272]="*Ekamidaṃ, āvuso, samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ ārabbha jātarūparajataṃ paṭikkhipi, sikkhāpadañca paññapesi.**“On one occasion at Rājagaha the Buddha prohibited gold, silver, and money and laid down a training rule because of Venerable Upananda the Sakyan.*";
P_HTM[14273]="*Evaṃvādī kirāhaṃ āyasmante upāsake saddhe pasanne akkosāmi, paribhāsāmi, appasādaṃ karomi;**It’s by speaking like this, it seems, that I’m abusing and reviling the venerable lay followers who have faith and confidence, and that I’m destroying their confidence,*";
P_HTM[14274]="*yohaṃ adhammaṃ adhammoti vadāmi, dhammaṃ dhammoti vadāmi, avinayaṃ avinayoti vadāmi, vinayaṃ vinayoti vadāmī”ti.**since I speak of what is contrary to the Teaching as contrary to the Teaching and of the Teaching as the Teaching, and since I speak of what is contrary to the Monastic Law as contrary to the Monastic Law and of the Monastic Law as the Monastic Law.”*";
P_HTM[14275]="*Evaṃ vutte, vesālikā upāsakā āyasmantaṃ yasaṃ kākaṇḍakaputtaṃ etadavocuṃ—**And the lay followers of Vesālī said to Yasa,*";
P_HTM[14276]="*“ekova, bhante, ayyo yaso kākaṇḍakaputto samaṇo sakyaputtiyo.**“Venerable, you’re the only Sakyan monastic;*";
P_HTM[14277]="*Sabbevime assamaṇā asakyaputtiyā.**none of these others is.*";
P_HTM[14278]="*Vasatu, bhante, ayyo yaso kākaṇḍakaputto vesāliyaṃ.**Please stay at Vesālī.*";
P_HTM[14279]="*Mayaṃ ayyassa yasassa kākaṇḍakaputtassa ussukkaṃ karissāma cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānan”ti.**We’ll do our best to supply you with robes, almsfood, a dwelling, and medicines.”*";
P_HTM[14280]="*Atha kho āyasmā yaso kākaṇḍakaputto vesālike upāsake saññāpetvā anudūtena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ ārāmaṃ agamāsi.**Having persuaded the lay followers of Vesālī, Yasa returned to the monastery together with his companion messenger.*";
P_HTM[14281]="*Atha kho vesālikā vajjiputtakā bhikkhū anudūtaṃ bhikkhuṃ pucchiṃsu—**Soon afterwards the Vajjian monks asked the monk who had been the companion messenger,*";
P_HTM[14282]="*“khamāpitāvuso, yasena kākaṇḍakaputtena vesālikā upāsakā”ti?**“Did Yasa ask the lay followers for forgiveness?”*";
P_HTM[14283]="*“Upāsakehi pāpikaṃ no, āvuso, kataṃ.**“The lay followers have acted badly toward us.*";
P_HTM[14284]="*Ekova yaso kākaṇḍakaputto samaṇo sakyaputtiyo kato.**They now regard Yasa as the only Sakyan a monastic,*";
P_HTM[14285]="*Sabbeva mayaṃ assamaṇā asakyaputtiyā katā”ti.**but none of us.”*";
P_HTM[14286]="*Atha kho vesālikā vajjiputtakā bhikkhū—**The Vajjian monks said,*";
P_HTM[14287]="*“ayaṃ, āvuso, yaso kākaṇḍakaputto amhehi asammato gihīnaṃ pakāsesi;**“Yasa has informed the householders without our approval.*";
P_HTM[14288]="*handassa mayaṃ ukkhepanīyakammaṃ karomā”ti.**Let’s do a legal procedure of ejection against him.”*";
P_HTM[14289]="*Te tassa ukkhepanīyakammaṃ kattukāmā sannipatiṃsu.**But when they gathered together to do the procedure against him,*";
P_HTM[14290]="*Atha kho āyasmā yaso kākaṇḍakaputto vehāsaṃ abbhuggantvā kosambiyaṃ paccuṭṭhāsi.**Yasa rose up into the air and landed at Kosambī.*";
P_HTM[14291]="*Atha kho āyasmā yaso kākaṇḍakaputto pāveyyakānañca avantidakkhiṇāpathakānañca bhikkhūnaṃ santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—**Yasa then sent a message to the monks at Pāvā and to the monks in Avantī in the southern region:*";
P_HTM[14292]="*“āgacchantu āyasmantā;**“Please come, Venerables.*";
P_HTM[14293]="*imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ ādiyissāma.**Let’s raise this legal issue—*";
P_HTM[14294]="*Pure adhammo dippati, dhammo paṭibāhiyyati;**before what is contrary to the Teaching shines forth and the Teaching is obstructed;*";
P_HTM[14295]="*avinayo dippati, vinayo paṭibāhiyyati;**before what is contrary to the Monastic Law shines forth and the Monastic Law is obstructed;*";
P_HTM[14296]="*pure adhammavādino balavanto honti, dhammavādino dubbalā honti;**before those who speak contrary to the Teaching become strong and those who speak in accordance with it become weak;*";
P_HTM[14297]="*avinayavādino balavanto honti, vinayavādino dubbalā hontī”ti.**before those who speak contrary to the Monastic Law become strong and those who speak in accordance with it become weak.”*";
P_HTM[14298]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā sambhūto sāṇavāsī ahogaṅge pabbate paṭivasati.**Yasa then traveled to Venerable Sambhūta Sāṇavāsī who was staying on the Ahogaṅga mountain.*";
P_HTM[14299]="*Atha kho āyasmā yaso kākaṇḍakaputto yena ahogaṅgo pabbato, yenāyasmā sambhūto sāṇavāsī tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ sambhūtaṃ sāṇavāsiṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**He bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[14300]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā yaso kākaṇḍakaputto āyasmantaṃ sambhūtaṃ sāṇavāsiṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[14301]="*“ime, bhante, vesālikā vajjiputtakā bhikkhū vesāliyaṃ dasa vatthūni dīpenti—**“Venerable, the Vajjian monks of Vesālī proclaim these ten practices as allowable:*";
P_HTM[14302]="*kappati siṅgiloṇakappo, kappati dvaṅgulakappo, kappati gāmantarakappo, kappati āvāsakappo, kappati anumatikappo, kappati āciṇṇakappo, kappati amathitakappo, kappati jaḷogiṃ pātuṃ, kappati adasakaṃ nisīdanaṃ, kappati jātarūparajatanti.**the salt-in-horn practice; the two fingerbreadths practice; the next-village practice; the many-monasteries practice; the consent practice; customary practices; the unchurned practice; palm-juice drinking; sitting mats without borders; and gold, silver, and money.*";
P_HTM[14303]="*Handa mayaṃ, bhante, imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ ādiyissāma.**Let’s raise this legal issue—*";
P_HTM[14304]="*Pure adhammo dippati, dhammo paṭibāhiyyati;**before what is contrary to the Teaching shines forth and the Teaching is obstructed;*";
P_HTM[14305]="*avinayo dippati, vinayo paṭibāhiyyati;**before what is contrary to the Monastic Law shines forth and the Monastic Law is obstructed;*";
P_HTM[14306]="*pure adhammavādino balavanto honti, dhammavādino dubbalā honti;**before those who speak contrary to the Teaching become strong and those who speak in accordance with it become weak;*";
P_HTM[14307]="*avinayavādino balavanto honti, vinayavādino dubbalā hontī”ti.**before those who speak contrary to the Monastic Law become strong and those who speak in accordance with it become weak.”*";
P_HTM[14308]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā sambhūto sāṇavāsī āyasmato yasassa kākaṇḍakaputtassa paccassosi.**“Yes.”*";
P_HTM[14309]="*Atha kho saṭṭhimattā pāveyyakā bhikkhū—**Soon afterwards, sixty monks from Pāvā—*";
P_HTM[14310]="*sabbe āraññikā, sabbe piṇḍapātikā, sabbe paṃsukūlikā, sabbe tecīvarikā, sabbeva arahanto—**all of them wilderness-dwellers, almsfood-only eaters, rag-robe wearers, three-robe owners, and perfected—*";
P_HTM[14311]="*ahogaṅge pabbate sannipatiṃsu.**gathered on mount Ahogaṅga.*";
P_HTM[14312]="*Aṭṭhāsītimattā avantidakkhiṇāpathakā bhikkhū—**And eighty-eight monks from Avantī in the southern region—*";
P_HTM[14313]="*appekacce āraññikā, appekacce piṇḍapātikā, appekacce paṃsukūlikā, appekacce tecīvarikā, sabbeva arahanto—**some of them wilderness-dwellers, some almsfood-only eaters, some rag-robe wearers, some three-robe owners, but all perfected—*";
P_HTM[14314]="*ahogaṅge pabbate sannipatiṃsu.**gathered on mount Ahogaṅga.*";
P_HTM[14315]="*Atha kho therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ mantayamānānaṃ etadahosi—**Then, as the senior monks were consulting one another, it occurred to them,*";
P_HTM[14316]="*“idaṃ kho adhikaraṇaṃ kakkhaḷañca, vāḷañca;**“This legal issue is going to be contentious and difficult.*";
P_HTM[14317]="*kaṃ nu kho mayaṃ pakkhaṃ labheyyāma, yena mayaṃ imasmiṃ adhikaraṇe balavantatarā assāmā”ti.**How can we get supporters, so that we will be stronger?”*";
P_HTM[14318]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā revato soreyye paṭivasati—**At this time Venerable Revata was staying at Soreyya.*";
P_HTM[14319]="*bahussuto āgatāgamo dhammadharo vinayadharo mātikādharo paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī lajjī kukkuccako sikkhākāmo.**He was learned and a master of the tradition; he was an expert on the Teaching, the Monastic Law, and the summaries; he was knowledgeable and competent, had a sense of conscience, and was afraid of wrongdoing and fond of the training.*";
P_HTM[14320]="*Atha kho therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The senior monks considered this*";
P_HTM[14321]="*“ayaṃ kho āyasmā revato soreyye paṭivasati—* **";
P_HTM[14322]="*bahussuto āgatāgamo dhammadharo vinayadharo mātikādharo paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī lajjī kukkuccako sikkhākāmo.* **";
P_HTM[14323]="*Sace mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ revataṃ pakkhaṃ labhissāma, evaṃ mayaṃ imasmiṃ adhikaraṇe balavantatarā assāmā”ti.**and said, “If we get Revata as a supporter, we’ll be stronger.”*";
P_HTM[14324]="*Assosi kho āyasmā revato—**Revata heard this conversation between the senior monks*";
P_HTM[14325]="*dibbāya sotadhātuyā visuddhāya atikkantamānusikāya—**by means of clairaudience,*";
P_HTM[14326]="*therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ mantayamānānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[14327]="*Sutvānassa etadahosi—**and he thought,*";
P_HTM[14328]="*“idaṃ kho adhikaraṇaṃ kakkhaḷañca vāḷañca.**“This legal issue is going to be contentious and difficult.*";
P_HTM[14329]="*Na kho metaṃ patirūpaṃ yohaṃ evarūpe adhikaraṇe osakkeyyaṃ.**It would not be appropriate for me to stay away from such a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[14330]="*Idāni ca pana te bhikkhū āgacchissanti.**But now these monks are coming,*";
P_HTM[14331]="*Sohaṃ tehi ākiṇṇo na phāsu gamissāmi.**and I won’t be at ease when they crowd me in.*";
P_HTM[14332]="*Yannūnāhaṃ paṭikacceva gaccheyyan”ti.**Let me leave before they arrive.”*";
P_HTM[14333]="*Atha kho āyasmā revato soreyyā saṅkassaṃ agamāsi.**And he went from Soreyya to Saṅkassa.*";
P_HTM[14334]="*Atha kho therā bhikkhū soreyyaṃ gantvā pucchiṃsu—**The senior monks went to Soreyya*";
P_HTM[14335]="*“kahaṃ āyasmā revato”ti?**and asked where Revata was.*";
P_HTM[14336]="*Te evamāhaṃsu—**They were told*";
P_HTM[14337]="*“esāyasmā revato saṅkassaṃ gato”ti.**that he had gone to Saṅkassa.*";
P_HTM[14338]="*Atha kho āyasmā revato saṅkassā kaṇṇakujjaṃ agamāsi.**Revata then went from Saṅkassa to Kaṇṇakujja.*";
P_HTM[14339]="*Atha kho therā bhikkhū saṅkassaṃ gantvā pucchiṃsu—**When the senior monks went to Saṅkassa*";
P_HTM[14340]="*“kahaṃ āyasmā revato”ti?**and asked where Revata was,*";
P_HTM[14341]="*Te evamāhaṃsu—**they were told*";
P_HTM[14342]="*“esāyasmā revato kaṇṇakujjaṃ gato”ti.**he had gone to Kaṇṇakujja.*";
P_HTM[14343]="*Atha kho āyasmā revato kaṇṇakujjā udumbaraṃ agamāsi.**And Revata went from Kaṇṇakujja to Udumbara.*";
P_HTM[14344]="*Atha kho therā bhikkhū kaṇṇakujjaṃ gantvā pucchiṃsu—**When the senior monks went to Kaṇṇakujja*";
P_HTM[14345]="*“kahaṃ āyasmā revato”ti?**and asked where Revata was,*";
P_HTM[14346]="*Te evamāhaṃsu—**they were told*";
P_HTM[14347]="*“esāyasmā revato udumbaraṃ gato”ti.**he had gone to Udumbara.*";
P_HTM[14348]="*Atha kho āyasmā revato udumbarā aggaḷapuraṃ agamāsi.**And Revata went from Udumbara to Aggaḷapura.*";
P_HTM[14349]="*Atha kho therā bhikkhū udumbaraṃ gantvā pucchiṃsu—**When the senior monks went to Udumbara*";
P_HTM[14350]="*“kahaṃ āyasmā revato”ti?**and asked where Revata was,*";
P_HTM[14351]="*Te evamāhaṃsu—**they were told*";
P_HTM[14352]="*“esāyasmā revato aggaḷapuraṃ gato”ti.**he had gone to Aggaḷapura.*";
P_HTM[14353]="*Atha kho āyasmā revato aggaḷapurā sahajātiṃ agamāsi.**And Revata went from Aggaḷapura to Sahajāti.*";
P_HTM[14354]="*Atha kho therā bhikkhū aggaḷapuraṃ gantvā pucchiṃsu—**When the senior monks went to Aggaḷapura*";
P_HTM[14355]="*“kahaṃ āyasmā revato”ti?**and asked where Revata was,*";
P_HTM[14356]="*Te evamāhaṃsu—**they were told*";
P_HTM[14357]="*“esāyasmā revato sahajātiṃ gato”ti.**he had gone to Sahajāti.*";
P_HTM[14358]="*Atha kho therā bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ revataṃ sahajātiyaṃ sambhāvesuṃ.**Finally the senior monks caught up with Revata at Sahajāti.*";
P_HTM[14359]="*Atha kho āyasmā sambhūto sāṇavāsī āyasmantaṃ yasaṃ kākaṇḍakaputtaṃ etadavoca—**Sambhūta Sāṇavāsī then said to Yasa,*";
P_HTM[14360]="*“ayaṃ, āvuso, āyasmā revato bahussuto āgatāgamo dhammadharo vinayadharo mātikādharo paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī lajjī kukkuccako sikkhākāmo.**“Revata is learned and a master of the tradition; he is an expert on the Teaching, on the Monastic Law, and on the summaries; he is knowledgeable and competent, has a sense of conscience, and is afraid of wrongdoing and fond of the training.*";
P_HTM[14361]="*Sace mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ revataṃ pañhaṃ pucchissāma, paṭibalo āyasmā revato ekeneva pañhena sakalampi rattiṃ vītināmetuṃ.**If we ask Revata a question, he would be capable of spending the whole night answering just that one.*";
P_HTM[14362]="*Idāni ca panāyasmā revato antevāsikaṃ sarabhāṇakaṃ bhikkhuṃ ajjhesissati.**Now, soon he will ask a pupil monk to chant.*";
P_HTM[14363]="*So tvaṃ tassa bhikkhuno sarabhaññapariyosāne āyasmantaṃ revataṃ upasaṅkamitvā imāni dasa vatthūni puccheyyāsī”ti.**Once the chanting is finished, go up to Revata and ask him about these ten practices.”*";
P_HTM[14364]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā yaso kākaṇḍakaputto āyasmato sambhūtassa sāṇavāsissa paccassosi.**“Yes.”*";
P_HTM[14365]="*Atha kho āyasmā revato antevāsikaṃ sarabhāṇakaṃ bhikkhuṃ ajjhesi.* **";
P_HTM[14366]="*Atha kho āyasmā yaso kākaṇḍakaputto tassa bhikkhuno sarabhaññapariyosāne yenāyasmā revato tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ revataṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Soon afterwards, when the chanting was finished, Yasa went up to Revata, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[14367]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā yaso kākaṇḍakaputto āyasmantaṃ revataṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[14368]="*“kappati, bhante, siṅgiloṇakappo”ti?**“Is the salt-in-horn practice allowable?”*";
P_HTM[14369]="*“Ko so, āvuso, siṅgiloṇakappo”ti?**“What is the salt-in-horn practice?”*";
P_HTM[14370]="*“Kappati, bhante, siṅginā loṇaṃ pariharituṃ—**“Is it allowable to carry salt in a horn*";
P_HTM[14371]="*yattha aloṇakaṃ bhavissati tattha paribhuñjissāmī”ti?**and then eat it whenever the food is unsalted?”*";
P_HTM[14372]="*“Nāvuso, kappatī”ti.**“No, it’s not allowable.”*";
P_HTM[14373]="*“Kappati, bhante, dvaṅgulakappo”ti?**“Is the two fingerbreadths practice allowable?”*";
P_HTM[14374]="*“Ko so, āvuso, dvaṅgulakappo”ti?**“What is the two fingerbreadths practice?”*";
P_HTM[14375]="*“Kappati, bhante, dvaṅgulāya chāyāya vītivattāya, vikāle bhojanaṃ bhuñjitun”ti?**“Is it allowable to eat at the wrong time, so long as the shadow of the sundial is within two fingerbreadths of midday?”*";
P_HTM[14376]="*“Nāvuso, kappatī”ti.**“No.”*";
P_HTM[14377]="*“Kappati, bhante, gāmantarakappo”ti?**“Is the next-village practice allowable?”*";
P_HTM[14378]="*“Ko so, āvuso, gāmantarakappo”ti?**“What is the next-village practice?”*";
P_HTM[14379]="*“Kappati, bhante—idāni gāmantaraṃ gamissāmīti—bhuttāvinā pavāritena anatirittaṃ bhojanaṃ bhuñjitun”ti?**“When you have finished your meal and refused an invitation to eat more, is it allowable to eat non-leftover food if you intend to go to the next village?”*";
P_HTM[14380]="*“Nāvuso, kappatī”ti.**“No.”*";
P_HTM[14381]="*“Kappati, bhante, āvāsakappo”ti?**“Is the many-monasteries practice allowable?”*";
P_HTM[14382]="*“Ko so, āvuso, āvāsakappo”ti?**“What is the many-monasteries practice?”*";
P_HTM[14383]="*“Kappati, bhante, sambahulā āvāsā samānasīmā nānuposathaṃ kātun”ti?**“When there are a number of monasteries within the same monastic boundary, is it allowable for them to do the observance-day procedure separately?”*";
P_HTM[14384]="*“Nāvuso, kappatī”ti.**“No.”*";
P_HTM[14385]="*“Kappati, bhante, anumatikappo”ti?**“Is the consent practice allowable?”*";
P_HTM[14386]="*“Ko so, āvuso, anumatikappo”ti?**“What is the consent practice?”*";
P_HTM[14387]="*“Kappati, bhante, vaggena saṅghena kammaṃ kātuṃ—**“Is it allowable to do a legal procedure with an incomplete Sangha,*";
P_HTM[14388]="*āgate bhikkhū anumānessāmā”ti?**with the intention of getting consent from the absent monks afterwards?”*";
P_HTM[14389]="*“Nāvuso, kappatī”ti.**“No.”*";
P_HTM[14390]="*“Kappati, bhante, āciṇṇakappo”ti?**“Are customary practices allowable?”*";
P_HTM[14391]="*“Ko so, āvuso, āciṇṇakappo”ti?**“What are customary practices?”*";
P_HTM[14392]="*“Kappati, bhante, idaṃ me upajjhāyena ajjhāciṇṇaṃ, idaṃ me ācariyena ajjhāciṇṇaṃ, taṃ ajjhācaritun”ti?**“Is it allowable to follow the practices of one’s preceptors or teachers?”*";
P_HTM[14393]="*“Āciṇṇakappo kho, āvuso, ekacco kappati, ekacco na kappatī”ti.**“Sometimes it is, sometimes it’s not.”*";
P_HTM[14394]="*“Kappati, bhante, amathitakappo”ti?**“Is the unchurned practice allowable?”*";
P_HTM[14395]="*“Ko so, āvuso, amathitakappo”ti?**“What is the unchurned practice?”*";
P_HTM[14396]="*“Kappati, bhante, yaṃ taṃ khīraṃ khīrabhāvaṃ vijahitaṃ, asampattaṃ dadhibhāvaṃ, taṃ bhuttāvinā pavāritena anatirittaṃ pātun”ti?**“When you have finished your meal and refused an invitation to eat more, is it allowable to drink that which is halfway between milk and curd, if it’s not leftover?”*";
P_HTM[14397]="*“Nāvuso, kappatī”ti?**“No.”*";
P_HTM[14398]="*“Kappati, bhante, jaḷogiṃ pātun”ti?**“Is palm-juice drinking allowable?”*";
P_HTM[14399]="*“Kā sā, āvuso, jaḷogī”ti?**“What is palm juice?”*";
P_HTM[14400]="*“Kappati, bhante, yā sā surā āsutā, asampattā majjabhāvaṃ, sā pātun”ti?**“Is it allowable to drink that which has started to ferment, but which hasn’t yet become a proper alcoholic drink?”*";
P_HTM[14401]="*“Nāvuso, kappatī”ti.**“No.”*";
P_HTM[14402]="*“Kappati, bhante, adasakaṃ nisīdanan”ti?**“Are sitting mats without borders allowable?”*";
P_HTM[14403]="*“Nāvuso, kappatī”ti.**“No.”*";
P_HTM[14404]="*“Kappati, bhante, jātarūparajatan”ti?**“Are gold, silver, and money allowable?”*";
P_HTM[14405]="*“Nāvuso, kappatī”ti.**“No.”*";
P_HTM[14406]="*“Ime, bhante, vesālikā vajjiputtakā bhikkhū vesāliyaṃ imāni dasa vatthūni dīpenti.**“The Vajjian monks of Vesālī proclaim these ten practices.*";
P_HTM[14407]="*Handa mayaṃ, bhante, imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ ādiyissāma.**Venerable, let’s raise this legal issue—*";
P_HTM[14408]="*Pure adhammo dippati, dhammo paṭibāhiyyati;**before what is contrary to the Teaching shines forth and the Teaching is obstructed;*";
P_HTM[14409]="*avinayo dippati, vinayo paṭibāhiyyati;**before what is contrary to the Monastic Law shines forth and the Monastic Law is obstructed;*";
P_HTM[14410]="*pure adhammavādino balavanto honti, dhammavādino dubbalā honti;**before those who speak contrary to the Teaching become strong and those who speak in accordance with it become weak;*";
P_HTM[14411]="*avinayavādino balavanto honti, vinayavādino dubbalā hontī”ti.**before those who speak contrary to the Monastic Law become strong and those who speak in accordance with it become weak.”*";
P_HTM[14412]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā revato āyasmato yasassa kākaṇḍakaputtassa paccassosi.**Saying, “Yes,” he consented to Yasa’s request.*";
P_HTM[14413]="*Paṭhamabhāṇavāro niṭṭhito.**The first section for recitation is finished.*";
P_HTM[14414]="*Assosuṃ kho vesālikā vajjiputtakā bhikkhū—**The Vajjian monks of Vesālī heard,*";
P_HTM[14415]="*“yaso kira kākaṇḍakaputto idaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ ādiyitukāmo pakkhaṃ pariyesati, labhati ca kira pakkhan”ti.**“It seems Yasa wants to raise this legal issue and is looking for supporters. And it seems he is gaining support.”*";
P_HTM[14416]="*Atha kho vesālikānaṃ vajjiputtakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**They said,*";
P_HTM[14417]="*“idaṃ kho adhikaraṇaṃ kakkhaḷañca vāḷañca.**“This legal issue is going to be contentious and difficult.*";
P_HTM[14418]="*Kaṃ nu kho mayaṃ pakkhaṃ labheyyāma, yena mayaṃ imasmiṃ adhikaraṇe balavantatarā assāmā”ti.**How can we get supporters, so that we will be stronger?”*";
P_HTM[14419]="*Atha kho vesālikānaṃ vajjiputtakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**And it occurred to them,*";
P_HTM[14420]="*“ayaṃ kho āyasmā revato bahussuto āgatāgamo dhammadharo vinayadharo mātikādharo paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī lajjī kukkuccako sikkhākāmo.**“Venerable Revata is learned and a master of the tradition; he is an expert on the Teaching, on the Monastic Law, and on the summaries; he is knowledgeable and competent, has a sense of conscience, and is afraid of wrongdoing and fond of the training.*";
P_HTM[14421]="*Sace mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ revataṃ pakkhaṃ labheyyāma, evaṃ mayaṃ imasmiṃ adhikaraṇe balavantatarā assāmā”ti.**If we get Revata as a supporter, we’ll be stronger.”*";
P_HTM[14422]="*Atha kho vesālikā vajjiputtakā bhikkhū pahūtaṃ sāmaṇakaṃ parikkhāraṃ paṭiyādesuṃ—**They prepared many monastic requisites:*";
P_HTM[14423]="*pattampi, cīvarampi, nisīdanampi, sūcigharampi, kāyabandhanampi, parissāvanampi, dhammakaraṇampi.**a bowl, a robe, a sitting mat, a needle case, a belt, a water filter, and a water strainer.*";
P_HTM[14424]="*Atha kho vesālikā vajjiputtakā bhikkhū taṃ sāmaṇakaṃ parikkhāraṃ ādāya nāvāya sahajātiṃ ujjaviṃsu;**Taking those requisites, they traveled by boat upstream to Sahajāti.*";
P_HTM[14425]="*nāvāya paccorohitvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle bhattavissaggaṃ karonti.**After disembarking, they had a meal at the foot of a tree.*";
P_HTM[14426]="*Atha kho āyasmato sāḷhassa rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi—**Just then Venerable Sāḷha was in seclusion, wondering,*";
P_HTM[14427]="*“ke nu kho dhammavādino—**“Who speak in accordance with the Teaching,*";
P_HTM[14428]="*pācīnakā vā bhikkhū, pāveyyakā vā”ti?**the monks from the east or the monks from Pāvā?”*";
P_HTM[14429]="*Atha kho āyasmato sāḷhassa, dhammañca vinayañca cetasā paccavekkhantassa, etadahosi—**Reflecting on the Teaching and the Monastic Law, it occurred to him,*";
P_HTM[14430]="*“adhammavādino pācīnakā bhikkhū, dhammavādino pāveyyakā bhikkhū”ti.**“The monks from the east speak contrary to the Teaching, but the monks from Pāvā don’t.”*";
P_HTM[14431]="*Atha kho aññatarā suddhāvāsakāyikā devatā āyasmato sāḷhassa cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya—**A god from the pure abodes read Sāḷha’s mind.*";
P_HTM[14432]="*seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—suddhāvāsesu devesu antarahitā āyasmato sāḷhassa sammukhe pāturahosi.**Then, just as a strong man might bend or stretch his arm, so too he disappeared from pure abodes and appeared in front of Sāḷha.*";
P_HTM[14433]="*Atha kho sā devatā āyasmantaṃ sāḷhaṃ etadavoca—**And he said to Sāḷha,*";
P_HTM[14434]="*“sādhu, bhante sāḷha, adhammavādī pācīnakā bhikkhū, dhammavādī pāveyyakā bhikkhū.**“You’re right, Venerable Sāḷha. The monks from the east speak contrary to the Teaching, but the monks from Pāvā don’t.*";
P_HTM[14435]="*Tena hi, bhante sāḷha, yathādhammo tathā tiṭṭhāhī”ti.**So then, take a stand in accordance with the Teaching.”*";
P_HTM[14436]="*“Pubbepi cāhaṃ, devate, etarahi ca yathādhammo tathā ṭhito;**“Both previously and now do I take a stand in accordance with the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[14437]="*api cāhaṃ na tāva diṭṭhiṃ āvi karomi, appeva nāma maṃ imasmiṃ adhikaraṇe sammanneyyā”ti.**But I won’t reveal my view in case I’m appointed to deal with this legal issue.”*";
P_HTM[14438]="*Atha kho vesālikā vajjiputtakā bhikkhū taṃ sāmaṇakaṃ parikkhāraṃ ādāya yenāyasmā revato tenupasaṅkamiṃsu, upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ revataṃ etadavocuṃ—**The Vajjian monks then went to Revata and said,*";
P_HTM[14439]="*“paṭiggaṇhātu, bhante, thero sāmaṇakaṃ parikkhāraṃ—**“Venerable, please accept these monastic requisites.”*";
P_HTM[14440]="*pattampi, cīvarampi, nisīdanampi, sūcigharampi, kāyabandhanampi, parissāvanampi, dhammakaraṇampī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[14441]="*“Alaṃ, āvuso, paripuṇṇaṃ me pattacīvaran”ti na icchi paṭiggahetuṃ.**Not wanting to accept them, he replied, “There is no need. My bowl and robes are complete.”*";
P_HTM[14442]="*Tena kho pana samayena uttaro nāma bhikkhu vīsativasso āyasmato revatassa upaṭṭhāko hoti.**At this time a monk called Uttara, who had twenty years of seniority, was Revata’s attendant.*";
P_HTM[14443]="*Atha kho vesālikā vajjiputtakā bhikkhū yenāyasmā uttaro tenupasaṅkamiṃsu, upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ uttaraṃ etadavocuṃ—**The Vajjian monks then went to him and said,*";
P_HTM[14444]="*“paṭiggaṇhātu āyasmā uttaro sāmaṇakaṃ parikkhāraṃ—**“Please accept these monastic requisites.”*";
P_HTM[14445]="*pattampi, cīvarampi, nisīdanampi, sūcigharampi, kāyabandhanampi, parissāvanampi, dhammakaraṇampī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[14446]="*“Alaṃ, āvuso, paripuṇṇaṃ me pattacīvaran”ti na icchi paṭiggahetuṃ.**Not wanting to accept them, he replied, “There is no need. My bowl and robes are complete.”*";
P_HTM[14447]="*“Manussā kho, āvuso uttara, bhagavato sāmaṇakaṃ parikkhāraṃ upanāmenti.**“People brought monastic requisites to the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[14448]="*Sace bhagavā paṭiggaṇhāti, teneva te attamanā honti.**If the Buddha received them, they were pleased.*";
P_HTM[14449]="*No ce bhagavā paṭiggaṇhāti, āyasmato ānandassa upanāmenti—**If he didn’t, they brought them to Venerable Ānanda instead,*";
P_HTM[14450]="*paṭiggaṇhātu, bhante, thero sāmaṇakaṃ parikkhāraṃ.**saying, ‘Venerable, please accept these monastic requisites.*";
P_HTM[14451]="*Yathā bhagavatā paṭiggahito, evameva so bhavissatīti.**It will be as if they’re received by the Buddha himself.’*";
P_HTM[14452]="*Paṭiggaṇhātu āyasmā uttaro sāmaṇakaṃ parikkhāraṃ.**So please accept these monastic requisites.*";
P_HTM[14453]="*Yathā therena paṭiggahito, evameva so bhavissatī”ti.**It will be as if they’re received by the elder himself.”*";
P_HTM[14454]="*Atha kho āyasmā uttaro vesālikehi vajjiputtehi bhikkhūhi nippīḷiyamāno ekaṃ cīvaraṃ aggahesi.**Because he was pressured, Uttara received one robe.*";
P_HTM[14455]="*“Vadeyyātha, āvuso, yena attho”ti.**And he said, “Please say what you want.”*";
P_HTM[14456]="*“Ettakaṃ āyasmā uttaro theraṃ vadetu;**“Please say this to the elder,*";
P_HTM[14457]="*ettakañca, bhante, thero saṅghamajjhe vadetu—**‘Sir, please say this in the midst of the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[14458]="*‘puratthimesu janapadesu buddhā bhagavanto uppajjanti.**“Buddhas appear in the eastern countries.*";
P_HTM[14459]="*Dhammavādī pācīnakā bhikkhū, adhammavādī pāveyyakā bhikkhū’”ti.**The monks from the east speak in accordance with the Teaching, not so the monks from Pāvā.”’”*";
P_HTM[14460]="*“Evamāvuso”ti**“Yes.”*";
P_HTM[14461]="*kho āyasmā uttaro vesālikānaṃ vajjiputtakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ paṭissutvā yenāyasmā revato tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ revataṃ etadavoca—**He then went to Revata*";
P_HTM[14462]="*“ettakaṃ, bhante, thero saṅghamajjhe vadetu—**and told him what he had been asked to say.*";
P_HTM[14463]="*‘puratthimesu janapadesu buddhā bhagavanto uppajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[14464]="*Dhammavādī pācīnakā bhikkhū, adhammavādī pāveyyakā bhikkhū’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[14465]="*“Adhamme maṃ tvaṃ, bhikkhu, niyojesī”ti thero āyasmantaṃ uttaraṃ paṇāmesi.**Revata replied, “You’re urging me to act contrary to the Teaching,” and he dismissed Uttara.*";
P_HTM[14466]="*Atha kho vesālikā vajjiputtakā bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ uttaraṃ etadavocuṃ—**Soon afterwards the Vajjian monks asked Uttara,*";
P_HTM[14467]="*“kiṃ, āvuso uttara, thero āhā”ti?**“What did he say?”*";
P_HTM[14468]="*“Pāpikaṃ no, āvuso, kataṃ.**“We have acted badly.*";
P_HTM[14469]="*‘Adhamme maṃ tvaṃ, bhikkhu, niyojesī’ti thero maṃ paṇāmesī”ti.**Saying, ‘You’re urging me to act contrary to the Teaching’, the elder dismissed me.”*";
P_HTM[14470]="*“Nanu tvaṃ, āvuso, vuḍḍho vīsativassosī”ti?**“Are you not a senior monk of twenty years’ standing?”*";
P_HTM[14471]="*“Āmāvuso, api ca mayaṃ garunissayaṃ gaṇhāmā”ti.**“Yes. Nevertheless, I live with formal support from him because I respect him.”*";
P_HTM[14472]="*Atha kho saṅgho taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vinicchinitukāmo sannipati.**The Sangha then gathered to deliberate on that legal issue.*";
P_HTM[14473]="*Atha kho āyasmā revato saṅghaṃ ñāpesi—**Revata informed the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[14474]="*“Suṇātu me, āvuso, saṅgho.**“Please, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[14475]="*Sace mayaṃ imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ idha vūpasamessāma, siyāpi mūlādāyakā bhikkhū punakammāya ukkoṭeyyuṃ.**If we were to resolve this legal issue here, it might be that the monks who started the ten practices would reopen it.*";
P_HTM[14476]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, yatthevimaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ samuppannaṃ, saṅgho tatthevimaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasameyyā”ti.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should resolve this legal issue in the place where it arose.”*";
P_HTM[14477]="*Atha kho therā bhikkhū vesāliṃ agamaṃsu—**The senior monks then went to Vesālī*";
P_HTM[14478]="*taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vinicchinitukāmā.**to deliberate on that legal issue.*";
P_HTM[14479]="*Tena kho pana samayena sabbakāmī nāma pathabyā saṅghatthero vīsavassasatiko upasampadāya, āyasmato ānandassa saddhivihāriko, vesāliyaṃ paṭivasati.**At that time there was a monk called Sabbakāmī who had been ordained for one hundred and twenty years and was the most senior monk in the world. He had been a student of Venerable Ānanda and was now staying at Vesālī.*";
P_HTM[14480]="*Atha kho āyasmā revato āyasmantaṃ sambhūtaṃ sāṇavāsiṃ etadavoca—**Revata said to Sambhūta Sāṇavāsī,*";
P_HTM[14481]="*“ahaṃ, āvuso, yasmiṃ vihāre sabbakāmī thero viharati, taṃ vihāraṃ upagacchāmi.**“I’ll be staying in Sabbakāmī’s dwelling.*";
P_HTM[14482]="*So tvaṃ kālasseva āyasmantaṃ sabbakāmiṃ upasaṅkamitvā imāni dasa vatthūni puccheyyāsī”ti.**Please go to Sabbakāmī at the appropriate time and ask about these ten practices.”*";
P_HTM[14483]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā sambhūto sāṇavāsī āyasmato revatassa paccassosi.**“Yes.”*";
P_HTM[14484]="*Atha kho āyasmā revato, yasmiṃ vihāre sabbakāmī thero viharati, taṃ vihāraṃ upagacchi.**Revata then entered Sabbakāmī’s dwelling.*";
P_HTM[14485]="*Gabbhe āyasmato sabbakāmissa senāsanaṃ paññattaṃ hoti, gabbhappamukhe āyasmato revatassa.**And Sabbakāmī had his resting place prepared in the room, whereas Revata had his prepared in the entryway.*";
P_HTM[14486]="*Atha kho āyasmā revato—**When Revata saw*";
P_HTM[14487]="*“ayaṃ thero mahallako na nipajjatī”ti—**that the old monk did not lie down,*";
P_HTM[14488]="*na seyyaṃ kappesi.**he too did not lie down.*";
P_HTM[14489]="*Āyasmā sabbakāmī—**And when Sabbakāmī saw*";
P_HTM[14490]="*“ayaṃ bhikkhu āgantuko kilanto na nipajjatī”ti—**that the tired monk who had just arrived did not lie down,*";
P_HTM[14491]="*na seyyaṃ kappesi.**he too did not lie down.*";
P_HTM[14492]="*Atha kho āyasmā sabbakāmī rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhāya āyasmantaṃ revataṃ etadavoca—**Getting up early in the morning, Sabbakāmī said to Revata,*";
P_HTM[14493]="*“katamena tvaṃ bhūmi vihārena etarahi bahulaṃ viharasī”ti?**“My friend, what’s your main meditation?”*";
P_HTM[14494]="*“Mettāvihārena kho ahaṃ, bhante, etarahi bahulaṃ viharāmī”ti.**“My main meditation, Sir, is good will.”*";
P_HTM[14495]="*“Kullakavihārena kira tvaṃ bhūmi etarahi bahulaṃ viharasi.**“Your meditation is noble,*";
P_HTM[14496]="*Kullakavihāro eso bhūmi yadidaṃ mettā”ti.**for good will is a noble meditation.”*";
P_HTM[14497]="*“Pubbepi me, bhante, gihibhūtassa āciṇṇā mettā.**“In the past, too, when I was a householder, I habitually practiced good will,*";
P_HTM[14498]="*Tenāhaṃ etarahipi mettāvihārena bahulaṃ viharāmi, api ca mayā cirappattaṃ arahattanti.**and now it’s my main meditation. Besides, I attained perfection long ago.*";
P_HTM[14499]="*Thero pana, bhante, katamena vihārena etarahi bahulaṃ viharatī”ti?**But what’s your main meditation?”*";
P_HTM[14500]="*“Suññatāvihārena kho ahaṃ bhūmi etarahi bahulaṃ viharāmī”ti.**“My main meditation is emptiness.”*";
P_HTM[14501]="*“Mahāpurisavihārena kira, bhante, thero etarahi bahulaṃ viharati.**“Your meditation is that of a great man,*";
P_HTM[14502]="*Mahāpurisavihāro eso, bhante, yadidaṃ suññatā”ti.**for emptiness is the meditation of a great man.”*";
P_HTM[14503]="*“Pubbepi me bhūmi gihibhūtassa āciṇṇā suññatā.**“In the past, too, when I was a householder, I habitually practiced emptiness,*";
P_HTM[14504]="*Tenāhaṃ etarahipi suññatāvihārena bahulaṃ viharāmi, api ca mayā cirappattaṃ arahattan”ti.**and now it’s my main meditation. Besides, I attained perfection long ago.”*";
P_HTM[14505]="*Ayañcarahi therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ antarākathā vippakatā, athāyasmā sambhūto sāṇavāsī tasmiṃ anuppatto hoti.**At that moment the conversation between the senior monks was interrupted because Sambhūta Sāṇavāsī arrived.*";
P_HTM[14506]="*Atha kho āyasmā sambhūto sāṇavāsī yenāyasmā sabbakāmī tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ sabbakāmiṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Sambhūta Sāṇavāsī went up to Sabbakāmī, bowed, sat down,*";
P_HTM[14507]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sambhūto sāṇavāsī āyasmantaṃ sabbakāmiṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[14508]="*“ime, bhante, vesālikā vajjiputtakā bhikkhū vesāliyaṃ dasa vatthūni dīpenti—**“Venerable, the Vajjian monks of Vesālī proclaim ten practices as allowable:*";
P_HTM[14509]="*kappati siṅgiloṇakappo, kappati dvaṅgulakappo, kappati gāmantarakappo, kappati āvāsakappo, kappati anumatikappo, kappati āciṇṇakappo, kappati amathitakappo, kappati jaḷogiṃ, pātuṃ kappati adasakaṃ nisīdanaṃ, kappati jātarūparajatanti.**the salt-in-horn practice; the two fingerbreadths practice; the next-village practice; the many-monasteries practice; the consent practice; customary practices; the unchurned practice; palm-juice drinking; sitting mats without borders; and gold, silver, and money.*";
P_HTM[14510]="*Therena, bhante, upajjhāyassa mūle bahudhammo ca vinayo ca pariyatto.**Now you have learned much, both of the Teaching and the Monastic Law, at the feet of your preceptor.*";
P_HTM[14511]="*Therassa, bhante, dhammañca vinayañca paccavekkhantassa kathaṃ hoti?**When you reflect on the Teaching and the Monastic Law,*";
P_HTM[14512]="*Ke nu kho dhammavādino—**who speaks in accordance with the Teaching,*";
P_HTM[14513]="*pācīnakā vā bhikkhū, pāveyyakā vā”ti?**the monks from the east or the monks from Pāvā?”*";
P_HTM[14514]="*“Tayāpi kho, āvuso, upajjhāyassa mūle bahu dhammo ca vinayo ca pariyatto.**“You too have learned much, both of the Teaching and the Monastic Law, at the feet of your preceptor.*";
P_HTM[14515]="*Tuyhaṃ pana, āvuso, dhammañca vinayañca paccavekkhantassa kathaṃ hoti?**When you reflect on the Teaching and the Monastic Law,*";
P_HTM[14516]="*Ke nu kho dhammavādino—**who speaks in accordance with the Teaching,*";
P_HTM[14517]="*pācīnakā vā bhikkhū, pāveyyakā vā”ti?**the monks from the east or the monks from Pāvā?”*";
P_HTM[14518]="*“Mayhaṃ kho, bhante, dhammañca vinayañca paccavekkhantassa evaṃ hoti—**“When I reflect like this, it occurs to me*";
P_HTM[14519]="*adhammavādī pācīnakā bhikkhū, dhammavādī pāveyyakā bhikkhūti;**that the monks from the east speak contrary to the Teaching, but the monks from Pāvā don’t.*";
P_HTM[14520]="*api cāhaṃ na tāva diṭṭhiṃ āvi karomi, appeva nāma maṃ imasmiṃ adhikaraṇe sammanneyyā”ti.**But I won’t reveal my view in case I’m appointed to deal with this legal issue.”*";
P_HTM[14521]="*“Mayhampi kho, āvuso, dhammañca vinayañca paccavekkhantassa evaṃ hoti—**“And when I reflect like this, it occurs to me too*";
P_HTM[14522]="*adhammavādī pācīnakā bhikkhū, dhammavādī pāveyyakā bhikkhūti;**that the monks from the east speak contrary to the Teaching, but the monks from Pāvā don’t.*";
P_HTM[14523]="*api cāhaṃ na tāva diṭṭhiṃ āvi karomi, appeva nāma maṃ imasmiṃ adhikaraṇe sammanneyyā”ti.**And I too won’t reveal my view in case I’m appointed to deal with this legal issue.”*";
P_HTM[14524]="*Atha kho saṅgho taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vinicchinitukāmo sannipati.**Then the Sangha gathered to deliberate on that legal issue.*";
P_HTM[14525]="*Tasmiṃ kho pana adhikaraṇe vinicchiyamāne anaggāni ceva bhassāni jāyanti, na cekassa bhāsitassa attho viññāyati.**While they were deliberating, there was endless talk, but not a single statement that could be understood.*";
P_HTM[14526]="*Atha kho āyasmā revato saṅghaṃ ñāpesi—**Revata then informed the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[14527]="*“Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**“Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[14528]="*Amhākaṃ imasmiṃ adhikaraṇe vinicchiyamāne anaggāni ceva bhassāni jāyanti, na cekassa bhāsitassa attho viññāyati.**While we were deliberating, there was endless talk, but not a single statement that could be understood.*";
P_HTM[14529]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ ubbāhikāya vūpasameyyā”ti.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should resolve this legal issue by means of a committee.”*";
P_HTM[14530]="*Saṅgho cattāro pācīnake bhikkhū, cattāro pāveyyake bhikkhū uccini.**The Sangha then selected four monks from the east—*";
P_HTM[14531]="*Pācīnakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ—* **";
P_HTM[14532]="*āyasmantañca sabbakāmiṃ, āyasmantañca sāḷhaṃ, āyasmantañca khujjasobhitaṃ, āyasmantañca vāsabhagāmikaṃ;**Venerable Sabbakāmī, Venerable Sāḷha, Venerable Khujjasobhita, and Venerable Vāsabhagāmika—*";
P_HTM[14533]="*pāveyyakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ—**and four monks from Pāvā—*";
P_HTM[14534]="*āyasmantañca revataṃ, āyasmantañca sambhūtaṃ sāṇavāsiṃ, āyasmantañca yasaṃ kākaṇḍakaputtaṃ, āyasmantañca sumananti.**Venerable Revata, Venerable Sambhūta Sāṇavāsī, Venerable Yasa of Kākaṇḍa, and Venerable Sumana.*";
P_HTM[14535]="*Atha kho āyasmā revato saṅghaṃ ñāpesi—**Revata then informed the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[14536]="*“Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**“Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[14537]="*Amhākaṃ imasmiṃ adhikaraṇe vinicchiyamāne anaggāni ceva bhassāni jāyanti, na cekassa bhāsitassa attho viññāyati.**While we were deliberating, there was endless talk, but not a single statement that could be understood.*";
P_HTM[14538]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho cattāro pācīnake bhikkhū, cattāro pāveyyake bhikkhū sammanneyya ubbāhikāya imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should appoint four monks from the east and four from Pāvā to resolve this legal issue by means of a committee.*";
P_HTM[14539]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[14540]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[14541]="*Amhākaṃ imasmiṃ adhikaraṇe vinicchiyamāne anaggāni ceva bhassāni jāyanti, na cekassa bhāsitassa attho viññāyati.**While we were deliberating, there was endless talk, but not a single statement that could be understood.*";
P_HTM[14542]="*Saṅgho cattāro pācīnake bhikkhū, cattāro pāveyyake bhikkhū sammannati ubbāhikāya imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**The Sangha appoints four monks from the east and four from Pāvā to resolve this legal issue by means of a committee.*";
P_HTM[14543]="*Yassāyasmato khamati catunnaṃ pācīnakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, catunnaṃ pāveyyakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ sammuti, ubbāhikāya imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of appointing four monks from the east and four from Pāvā to resolve this legal issue by means of a committee should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[14544]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[14545]="*Sammatā saṅghena cattāro pācīnakā bhikkhū, cattāro pāveyyakā bhikkhū, ubbāhikāya imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasametuṃ.**The Sangha has appointed four monks from the east and four from Pāvā to resolve this legal issue by means of a committee.*";
P_HTM[14546]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[14547]="*Tena kho pana samayena ajito nāma bhikkhu dasavasso saṅghassa pātimokkhuddesako hoti.**At that time there was a monk called Ajita who had ten years of seniority and was the Sangha’s reciter of the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[14548]="*Atha kho saṅgho āyasmantampi ajitaṃ sammannati—**The Sangha appointed him*";
P_HTM[14549]="*therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ āsanapaññāpakaṃ.**to assign seats to the senior monks.*";
P_HTM[14550]="*Atha kho therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The senior monks said,*";
P_HTM[14551]="*“kattha nu kho mayaṃ imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasameyyāmā”ti?**“Where should we resolve this legal issue?”*";
P_HTM[14552]="*Atha kho therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**It occurred to them,*";
P_HTM[14553]="*“ayaṃ kho vālikārāmo ramaṇīyo appasaddo appanigghoso.**“There is the Vālika Monastery, which is delightful, quiet, and free from chatter.*";
P_HTM[14554]="*Yannūna mayaṃ vālikārāme imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasameyyāmā”ti.**Let’s resolve this legal issue there.”*";
P_HTM[14555]="*Atha kho therā bhikkhū vālikārāmaṃ agamaṃsu—**And they went to the Vālika Monastery*";
P_HTM[14556]="*taṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vinicchinitukāmā.**to deliberate on that legal issue.*";
P_HTM[14557]="*Atha kho āyasmā revato saṅghaṃ ñāpesi—**Revata then informed the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[14558]="*“Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**“Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[14559]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, ahaṃ āyasmantaṃ sabbakāmiṃ vinayaṃ puccheyyan”ti.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, I will question Venerable Sabbakāmī on the Monastic Law.”*";
P_HTM[14560]="*Āyasmā sabbakāmī saṅghaṃ ñāpesi—**And Sabbakāmī informed the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[14561]="*“Suṇātu me, āvuso, saṅgho.**“Please, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[14562]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, ahaṃ revatena vinayaṃ puṭṭho vissajjeyyan”ti.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, I will reply when asked by Revata about the Monastic Law.”*";
P_HTM[14563]="*Atha kho āyasmā revato āyasmantaṃ sabbakāmiṃ etadavoca—**Revata said to Sabbakāmī,*";
P_HTM[14564]="*“kappati, bhante, siṅgiloṇakappo”ti?**“Sir, is the salt-in-horn practice allowable?”*";
P_HTM[14565]="*“Ko so, āvuso, siṅgiloṇakappo”ti?**“What is the salt-in-horn practice?”*";
P_HTM[14566]="*“Kappati, bhante, siṅginā loṇaṃ pariharituṃ—**“Is it allowable to carry salt in a horn*";
P_HTM[14567]="*yattha aloṇakaṃ bhavissati tattha paribhuñjissāmā”ti?**and then eat it whenever the food is unsalted?”*";
P_HTM[14568]="*“Nāvuso, kappatī”ti.**“No, it’s not allowable.”*";
P_HTM[14569]="*“ Kattha paṭikkhittan”ti?**“Where was it prohibited?”*";
P_HTM[14570]="*“Sāvatthiyaṃ, suttavibhaṅge”ti.**“At Sāvatthī, in the analysis of the Monastic Code.”*";
P_HTM[14571]="*“Kiṃ āpajjatī”ti?**“What was committed?”*";
P_HTM[14572]="*“Sannidhikārakabhojane pācittiyan”ti.**“An offense entailing confession for eating what has been stored.”*";
P_HTM[14573]="*“Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**“Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[14574]="*Idaṃ paṭhamaṃ vatthu saṅghena vinicchitaṃ.**The Sangha has decided on the first practice.*";
P_HTM[14575]="*Itipidaṃ vatthu uddhammaṃ, ubbinayaṃ, apagatasatthusāsanaṃ.**This practice is contrary to the Teaching, contrary to the Monastic Law, and a departure from the Teacher’s instruction.*";
P_HTM[14576]="*Idaṃ paṭhamaṃ salākaṃ nikkhipāmi”.**I make a note of the first decision.”*";
P_HTM[14577]="*“Kappati, bhante, dvaṅgulakappo”ti?**“Is the two fingerbreadths practice allowable?”*";
P_HTM[14578]="*“Ko so, āvuso, dvaṅgulakappo”ti?**“What is the two fingerbreadths practice?”*";
P_HTM[14579]="*“Kappati, bhante, dvaṅgulāya chāyāya vītivattāya vikāle bhojanaṃ bhuñjitun”ti?**“Is it allowable to eat at the wrong time, so long as the shadow of the sundial is within two fingerbreadths of midday?”*";
P_HTM[14580]="*“Nāvuso, kappatī”ti.**“No.”*";
P_HTM[14581]="*“ Kattha paṭikkhittan”ti?**“Where was it prohibited?”*";
P_HTM[14582]="*“Rājagahe, suttavibhaṅge”ti.**“At Rājagaha, in the analysis of the Monastic Code.”*";
P_HTM[14583]="*“Kiṃ āpajjatī”ti?**“What was committed?”*";
P_HTM[14584]="*“Vikālabhojane pācittiyan”ti.**“An offense entailing confession for eating at the wrong time.”*";
P_HTM[14585]="*“Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**“Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[14586]="*Idaṃ dutiyaṃ vatthu saṅghena vinicchitaṃ.**The Sangha has decided on the second practice.*";
P_HTM[14587]="*Itipidaṃ vatthu uddhammaṃ, ubbinayaṃ, apagatasatthusāsanaṃ.**This practice is contrary to the Teaching, contrary to the Monastic Law, and a departure from the Teacher’s instruction.*";
P_HTM[14588]="*Idaṃ dutiyaṃ salākaṃ nikkhipāmi”.**I make a note of the second decision.”*";
P_HTM[14589]="*“Kappati, bhante, gāmantarakappo”ti?**“Is the next-village practice allowable?”*";
P_HTM[14590]="*“Ko so, āvuso, gāmantarakappo”ti?**“What is the next-village practice?”*";
P_HTM[14591]="*“Kappati, bhante—idāni gāmantaraṃ gamissāmīti—bhuttāvinā pavāritena anatirittaṃ bhojanaṃ bhuñjitun”ti?**“When you have finished your meal and refused an invitation to eat more, is it allowable to eat non-leftover food if you intend to go to the next village?”*";
P_HTM[14592]="*“Nāvuso, kappatī”ti.**“No.”*";
P_HTM[14593]="*“Kattha paṭikkhittan”ti?**“Where was it prohibited?”*";
P_HTM[14594]="*“Sāvatthiyaṃ, suttavibhaṅge”ti.**“At Sāvatthī, in the analysis of the Monastic Code.”*";
P_HTM[14595]="*“Kiṃ āpajjatī”ti?**“What was committed?”*";
P_HTM[14596]="*“Anatirittabhojane pācittiyan”ti.**“An offense entailing confession for eating what is not left over.”*";
P_HTM[14597]="*“Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**“Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[14598]="*Idaṃ tatiyaṃ vatthu saṅghena vinicchitaṃ.**The Sangha has decided on the third practice.*";
P_HTM[14599]="*Itipidaṃ vatthu uddhammaṃ, ubbinayaṃ, apagatasatthusāsanaṃ.**This practice is contrary to the Teaching, contrary to the Monastic Law, and a departure from the Teacher’s instruction.*";
P_HTM[14600]="*Idaṃ tatiyaṃ salākaṃ nikkhipāmi”.**I make a note of the third decision.”*";
P_HTM[14601]="*“Kappati, bhante, āvāsakappo”ti?**“Is the many-monasteries practice allowable?”*";
P_HTM[14602]="*“Ko so, āvuso, āvāsakappo”ti?**“What is the many-monasteries practice?”*";
P_HTM[14603]="*“Kappati, bhante, sambahulā āvāsā samānasīmā nānuposathaṃ kātun”ti.**“When there are a number of monasteries within the same monastic boundary, is it allowable to do the observance-day procedure separately?”*";
P_HTM[14604]="*“Nāvuso, kappatī”ti.**“No.”*";
P_HTM[14605]="*“ Kattha paṭikkhittan”ti?**“Where was it prohibited?”*";
P_HTM[14606]="*“Rājagahe, uposathasaṃyutte”ti.**“At Rājagaha, in what is connected to the observance-day procedure.”*";
P_HTM[14607]="*“Kiṃ āpajjatī”ti?**“What was committed?”*";
P_HTM[14608]="*“Vinayātisāre dukkaṭan”ti.**“An act of wrong conduct for going beyond the Monastic Law.”*";
P_HTM[14609]="*“Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**“Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[14610]="*Idaṃ catutthaṃ vatthu saṅghena vinicchitaṃ.**The Sangha has decided on the fourth practice.*";
P_HTM[14611]="*Itipidaṃ vatthu uddhammaṃ, ubbinayaṃ, apagatasatthusāsanaṃ.**This practice is contrary to the Teaching, contrary to the Monastic Law, and a departure from the Teacher’s instruction.*";
P_HTM[14612]="*Idaṃ catutthaṃ salākaṃ nikkhipāmi”.**I make a note of the fourth decision.”*";
P_HTM[14613]="*“Kappati, bhante, anumatikappo”ti?**“Is the consent practice allowable?”*";
P_HTM[14614]="*“Ko so, āvuso, anumatikappo”ti?**“What is the consent practice?”*";
P_HTM[14615]="*“Kappati, bhante, vaggena saṅghena kammaṃ kātuṃ—**“Is it allowable to do a legal procedure with an incomplete Sangha,*";
P_HTM[14616]="*āgate bhikkhū anumānessāmā”ti?**with the intention of getting consent from the absent monks afterwards?”*";
P_HTM[14617]="*“Nāvuso, kappatī”ti.**“No.”*";
P_HTM[14618]="*“ Kattha paṭikkhittan”ti?**“Where was it prohibited?”*";
P_HTM[14619]="*“Campeyyake, vinayavatthusmin”ti.**“In the section on Those from Campā, in the Monastic Law.”*";
P_HTM[14620]="*“Kiṃ āpajjatī”ti?**“What was committed?”*";
P_HTM[14621]="*“Vinayātisāre dukkaṭan”ti.**“An act of wrong conduct for going beyond the Monastic Law.”*";
P_HTM[14622]="*“Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**“Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[14623]="*Idaṃ pañcamaṃ vatthu saṅghena vinicchitaṃ.**The Sangha has decided on the fifth practice.*";
P_HTM[14624]="*Itipidaṃ vatthu uddhammaṃ, ubbinayaṃ, apagatasatthusāsanaṃ.**This practice is contrary to the Teaching, contrary to the Monastic Law, and a departure from the Teacher’s instruction.*";
P_HTM[14625]="*Idaṃ pañcamaṃ salākaṃ nikkhipāmi”.**I make a note of the fifth decision.”*";
P_HTM[14626]="*“Kappati, bhante, āciṇṇakappo”ti?**“Are customary practices allowable?”*";
P_HTM[14627]="*“Ko so, āvuso, āciṇṇakappo”ti?**“What are customary practices?”*";
P_HTM[14628]="*“Kappati, bhante—**“Is it allowable*";
P_HTM[14629]="*idaṃ me upajjhāyena ajjhāciṇṇaṃ, idaṃ me ācariyena ajjhāciṇṇaṃ—**to follow the practices of one’s preceptors or teachers?”*";
P_HTM[14630]="*taṃ ajjhācaritun”ti?* **";
P_HTM[14631]="*“Āciṇṇakappo kho, āvuso, ekacco kappati, ekacco na kappatī”ti.**“Sometimes it is, sometimes it’s not.”*";
P_HTM[14632]="*“Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**“Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[14633]="*Idaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ vatthu saṅghena vinicchitaṃ.**The Sangha has decided on the sixth practice.*";
P_HTM[14634]="*Itipidaṃ vatthu uddhammaṃ, ubbinayaṃ, apagatasatthusāsanaṃ.**This practice is contrary to the Teaching, contrary to the Monastic Law, and a departure from the Teacher’s instruction.*";
P_HTM[14635]="*Idaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ salākaṃ nikkhipāmi”.**I make a note of the sixth decision.”*";
P_HTM[14636]="*“Kappati, bhante, amathitakappo”ti?**“Is the unchurned practice allowable?”*";
P_HTM[14637]="*“Ko so, āvuso, amathitakappo”ti?**“What is the unchurned practice?”*";
P_HTM[14638]="*“Kappati, bhante, yaṃ taṃ khīraṃ khīrabhāvaṃ vijahitaṃ, asampattaṃ dadhibhāvaṃ, taṃ bhuttāvinā pavāritena anatirittaṃ pātun”ti?**“When you have finished your meal and refused an invitation to eat more, is it allowable to drink that which is halfway between milk and curd, if it’s not leftover?”*";
P_HTM[14639]="*“Nāvuso, kappatī”ti.**“No.”*";
P_HTM[14640]="*“ Kattha paṭikkhittan”ti?**“Where was it prohibited?”*";
P_HTM[14641]="*“Sāvatthiyaṃ, suttavibhaṅge”ti.**“At Sāvatthī, in the analysis of the Monastic Code.”*";
P_HTM[14642]="*“Kiṃ āpajjatī”ti?**“What was committed?”*";
P_HTM[14643]="*“Anatirittabhojane pācittiyan”ti.**“An offense entailing confession for eating what is not left over.”*";
P_HTM[14644]="*“Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**“Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[14645]="*Idaṃ sattamaṃ vatthu saṅghena vinicchitaṃ.**The Sangha has decided on the seventh practice.*";
P_HTM[14646]="*Itipidaṃ vatthu uddhammaṃ, ubbinayaṃ, apagatasatthusāsanaṃ.**This practice is contrary to the Teaching, contrary to the Monastic Law, and a departure from the Teacher’s instruction.*";
P_HTM[14647]="*Idaṃ sattamaṃ salākaṃ nikkhipāmi”.**I make a note of the seventh decision.”*";
P_HTM[14648]="*“Kappati, bhante, jaḷogiṃ pātun”ti?**“Is palm-juice drinking allowable?”*";
P_HTM[14649]="*“Kā sā, āvuso, jaḷogī”ti?**“What is palm juice?”*";
P_HTM[14650]="*“Kappati, bhante, yā sā surā āsutā asampattā majjabhāvaṃ, sā pātun”ti?**“Is it allowable to drink that which has started to ferment, but which has not yet become a proper alcoholic drink?”*";
P_HTM[14651]="*“Nāvuso, kappatī”ti.**“No.”*";
P_HTM[14652]="*“ Kattha paṭikkhittan”ti?**“Where was it prohibited?”*";
P_HTM[14653]="*“Kosambiyaṃ, suttavibhaṅge”ti.**“At Kosambī, in the analysis of the Monastic Code.”*";
P_HTM[14654]="*“Kiṃ āpajjatī”ti.**“What was committed?”*";
P_HTM[14655]="*“Surāmerayapāne pācittiyan”ti.**“An offense entailing confession for drinking alcohol.”*";
P_HTM[14656]="*“Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**“Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[14657]="*Idaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ vatthu saṅghena vinicchitaṃ.**The Sangha has decided on the eighth practice.*";
P_HTM[14658]="*Itipidaṃ vatthu uddhammaṃ, ubbinayaṃ, apagatasatthusāsanaṃ.**This practice is contrary to the Teaching, contrary to the Monastic Law, and a departure from the Teacher’s instruction.*";
P_HTM[14659]="*Idaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ salākaṃ nikkhipāmi”.**I make a note of the eighth decision.”*";
P_HTM[14660]="*“Kappati, bhante, adasakaṃ nisīdanan”ti?**“Are sitting mats without borders allowable?”*";
P_HTM[14661]="*“Nāvuso, kappatī”ti.**“No.”*";
P_HTM[14662]="*“ Kattha paṭikkhittan”ti?**“Where was it prohibited?”*";
P_HTM[14663]="*“Sāvatthiyaṃ, suttavibhaṅge”ti.**“At Sāvatthī, in the analysis of the Monastic Code.”*";
P_HTM[14664]="*“Kiṃ āpajjatī”ti?**“What was committed?”*";
P_HTM[14665]="*“Chedanake pācittiyan”ti.**“An offense entailing confession in relation to the rule concerning cutting.”*";
P_HTM[14666]="*“Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**“Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[14667]="*Idaṃ navamaṃ vatthu saṅghena vinicchitaṃ.**The Sangha has decided on the ninth practice.*";
P_HTM[14668]="*Itipidaṃ vatthu uddhammaṃ, ubbinayaṃ, apagatasatthusāsanaṃ.**This practice is contrary to the Teaching, contrary to the Monastic Law, and a departure from the Teacher’s instruction.*";
P_HTM[14669]="*Idaṃ navamaṃ salākaṃ nikkhipāmi”.**I make a note of the ninth decision.”*";
P_HTM[14670]="*“Kappati, bhante, jātarūparajatan”ti?**“Are gold, silver, and money allowable?”*";
P_HTM[14671]="*“Nāvuso, kappatī”ti.**“No.”*";
P_HTM[14672]="*“ Kattha paṭikkhittan”ti.**“Where was it prohibited?”*";
P_HTM[14673]="*“Rājagahe, suttavibhaṅge”ti.**“At Rājagaha, in the analysis of the Monastic Code.”*";
P_HTM[14674]="*“Kiṃ āpajjatī”ti?**“What was committed?”*";
P_HTM[14675]="*“Jātarūparajatapaṭiggahaṇe pācittiyan”ti.**“An offense entailing confession for receiving gold, silver, or money.”*";
P_HTM[14676]="*“Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**“Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[14677]="*Idaṃ dasamaṃ vatthu saṅghena vinicchitaṃ.**The Sangha has decided on the tenth practice.*";
P_HTM[14678]="*Itipidaṃ vatthu uddhammaṃ, ubbinayaṃ, apagatasatthusāsanaṃ.**This practice is contrary to the Teaching, contrary to the Monastic Law, and a departure from the Teacher’s instruction.*";
P_HTM[14679]="*Idaṃ dasamaṃ salākaṃ nikkhipāmi.**I make a note of the tenth decision.*";
P_HTM[14680]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[14681]="*Imāni dasa vatthūni saṅghena vinicchitāni.**The Sangha has decided on the ten practices.*";
P_HTM[14682]="*Itipimāni dasavatthūni uddhammāni, ubbinayāni, apagatasatthusāsanānī”ti.**These ten practices are contrary to the Teaching, contrary to the Monastic Law, and a departure from the Teacher’s instruction.”*";
P_HTM[14683]="*“Nihatametaṃ, āvuso, adhikaraṇaṃ, santaṃ vūpasantaṃ suvūpasantaṃ.**“The legal issue has been settled and properly resolved.*";
P_HTM[14684]="*Api ca maṃ tvaṃ, āvuso, saṅghamajjhepi imāni dasa vatthūni puccheyyāsi—tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ saññattiyā”ti.**Nevertheless, for the purpose of convincing the other monks, you should ask me about these ten practices also in the midst of the Sangha.”*";
P_HTM[14685]="*Atha kho āyasmā revato āyasmantaṃ sabbakāmiṃ saṅghamajjhepi imāni dasa vatthūni pucchi.**Revata then asked Sabbakāmī about these ten practices in the midst of the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[14686]="*Puṭṭho puṭṭho āyasmā sabbakāmī vissajjesi.**And Sabbakāmī was able to reply to every question.*";
P_HTM[14687]="*Imāya kho pana vinayasaṅgītiyā satta bhikkhusatāni anūnāni anadhikāni ahesuṃ, tasmāyaṃ vinayasaṅgīti “sattasatikā”ti vuccatīti.**At this communal recitation of the Monastic Law there were seven hundred monks, neither more nor less. For this reason this communal recitation is called “The group of seven hundred”.*";
P_HTM[14688]="*Sattasatikakkhandhako dvādasamo. Imamhi khandhake vatthū pañcavīsati.**The twelfth chapter on the group of seven hundred is finished. In this chapter there are twenty-five topics.*";
P_HTM[14689]="*Tassuddānaṃ* **";
P_HTM[14690]="*Dasa vatthūni pūretvā,* **";
P_HTM[14691]="*kammaṃ dūtena pāvisi;* **";
P_HTM[14692]="*Cattāro puna rūpañca,* **";
P_HTM[14693]="*kosambi ca pāveyyako.* **";
P_HTM[14694]="*Maggo soreyyaṃ saṅkassaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[14695]="*kaṇṇakujjaṃ udumbaraṃ;* **";
P_HTM[14696]="*Sahajāti ca majjhesi,* **";
P_HTM[14697]="*assosi kaṃ nu kho mayaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[14698]="*Pattanāvāya ujjavi,* **";
P_HTM[14699]="*rahosi upanāmayaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[14700]="*Garu saṅgho ca vesāliṃ,* **";
P_HTM[14701]="*mettā saṅgho ubbāhikāti.* **";
P_HTM[14702]="*Sattasatikakkhandhako niṭṭhito.**The chapter on the group of seven hundred is finished.*";
P_HTM[14703]="*Cūḷavaggo niṭṭhito.**The Short Division is finished.*";
P_HTM[14704]="*Cūḷavaggapāḷi niṭṭhitā.**The canonical text of the Short Division is finished.*";
